Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Coody is changing the consulting industry with a new model designed to benefit the individual, not the consulting company. We do this by combining the benefits of being a freelancer with the security of a traditional employment.

This means that we pay the best salary in the industry, provide fantastic benefits while at the same time being a secure workplace with a fixed monthly salary, stable employment terms and above all - a wonderful community and really good exchange of knowledge.

Why chose when you can have both?

We have simply stripped away all unnecessary overhead between yourself and the company to be able to offer you a platform that will help you achieve your priorities in life and at the same time work on meaningful projects for some of the country's most exciting digital leaders.

(We do work for companies such as Spotify, Mathem, Hemnet, Bokio, Polestar, Tobii and others).

WE ARE HIRING DATA SCIENTISTS TO BE PART OF CHANGING THE WORLD OF CONSULTING TOGETHER WITH COODY AND OUR CLIENTS!

What we look for

We are looking for data scientists to work together with our exciting clients who are leading products companies, startups and scaleups. You’ll work as an integral part of our clients team to solve complex business challenges together with engineers, developers and designers.

You have previous professional experience from data science or machine learning, and a relevant educational background. When working as a consultant with Coody it’s crucial that you are communicative and can work well with others.

Your background

Extensive knowledge in Python, R and machine learning.
Experience from building data pipelines and ML models with some of the major cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, GCP).
English fluently, spoken and written.
What we offer

We offer you an opportunity to work with exciting challenges and projects with our clients where your work will impact a great number of users.

At your service is an experienced sales-team with best-in-industry tools and the right network to find you the perfect assignment and give you the best time of your career!

You will focus on working on longer assignments for between 6 months to 3 years, that will both challenge your knowledge and give you the best possible use of your skill set. You will work as an integral part of the client’s organization, remote or on-site. We do not work with customers in morally dubious industries.

We have a limit on quarterly hires - so don’t wait. Send us your application and get in contact with us in a blink of an eye!

Title: Chief Data Scientist
Description:
Datatera bridges the gap between healthcare and technology by providing HealthTech companies access to high-quality, real-world Health data which enables them to create accurate AI models that will elevate healthcare innovation and increase value for patients.

We are searching for someone who is passionate about Health Data and willing to take the role of Chief Data Scientist to help us with building our AI Module and being the key person in our Data Science strategy and working closely with the CTO.

This role requires;

Having at least 5+ years of experience with Data Science and AI
Having an entrepreneurial/creative mind and belief in the company's vision
Having prior Health Data experience is definitely a big plus
Having a good work ethic & good communication skills are equally important
Looking forward to receiving your application.

P.S. We don't have any intention to collaborate with Recruitment Agencies for this role.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Stadium utökar sitt Data & Analytics team och letar efter en Data Scientist.
Är du vår nästa stjärnspelare?
Har du ett stort intresse för avancerad analys och AI och tycker att retail och Stadium verkar spännande? Vill du vara en del av ett innovativt team och kunna bidra till att utveckla Stadiums strategiska position? Då är du personen vi letar efter.
Vad innebär det att vara Data Scientist?
Som Data Scientist på Stadium kommer du att ansvara för att genomföra analyser, skapa insikter och förmedla vidare dessa till organisationen. Du kommer att designa, utveckla och utvärdera avancerade prediktiva modeller. Du är en affärsdriven person som får energi av att dra slutsatser ur stora datamängder och gillar att jobba nära verksamheten. Du har med fördel erfarenhet från retail eller andra större bolag.
Rollen innebär att du arbetar som informations- och insiktspecialist mot hela organisationen. Du kommer att använda Machine Learning och statistiska metoder för att ta fram skalbara lösningar på problem.
Förutom ovanstående nämnda uppgifter kommer ditt övergripande ansvar innebära att:
Vara en nyckelperson i flertalet projekt och crossfunktionella team.
Skapa dashboards, segmenteringar och rapporteringslösningar som på ett effektivt sätt kan kommuniceras till verksamheten.
Identifiera, analysera och tolka trender/mönster i komplexa datamängder.
Tillämpa och utveckla prediktiva modeller.

Vem är du?
För att lyckas i rollen är du en social person med en positiv inställning och ett bra driv. Det är viktigt att du är en lagspelare och tror på samarbete, men samtidigt känner dig trygg med att jobba självständigt. Vi ser gärna att du har ett stort kundfokus och alltid strävar efter att leverera hög kvalitet. Tjänsten kräver att du behärskar engelska och svenska i både tal och skrift.
Du har relevant akademisk utbildning inom exempelvis matematik, statistik eller liknande.
Du har bra förståelse för data science och kunskaper om tillämpning av statistiska metoder.
Du har erfarenhet av analysverktyg som R/Python och SQL.
Du är insiktsdriven och kundorienterad.
Rollen innebär en unik möjlighet till att kombinera din analytiska sida med ditt kommersiella driv. Du kommer att bli en del av ett kvalificerat analysteam med målet att vidareutveckla organisationen genom insikter och data science.
Varaktighet/arbetstid
Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning med tillträde enligt överenskommelse. Provanställning tillämpas.
Ansökan
Ansökan Som en del i rekryteringsprocessen kommer du att få en inbjudan till din e-mail till att besvara ett personlighetstest och ett kapacitetstest. Det tar ca 30 minuter att besvara testen.
Eftersom vi alltid vill vara på tårna och göra saker så enkelt som möjligt är det inte säkert att vi väntar till sista ansökningsdag innan vi går vidare i rekryteringsprocessen. Så vänta inte med din ansökan utan sök redan idag!
Välkommen med din ansökan. Come join the movement!

Vi har riktigt bra förmåner
En arbetsplats där alla är välkomna
Utbildning och utveckling
Gemenskap och glädje
Rättvis och marknadsmässig lön
Träningsbidrag
Personalrabatt

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
At Tetra Pak we commit to making food safe and available, everywhere; and we protect what's good – protecting food, protecting people, and protecting the planet. By doing so we touch millions of people's lives every day. And we need people like you to make it happen.
Job Summary
We are looking for a Data Scientist, who will belong to the Tetra Pak´s Decision Science Team. You will participate in various projects, influence business decisions, and drive digital transformation at one of the largest consumer packaging companies in the world.

This position will be placed in Lund, Sweden.
What you will do
Participate in data science projects, be hands-on and build statistical models and determine optimal modeling approach for each business scenario
Oversee junior data scientists
Development, test, implement and deployment of data science solutions to solve various business issues.
Work closely with Sr. Data Scientists, and Data Scientist Managers, Business stakeholders and subject matter experts to review expected outputs and applicability to business challenge.
Identify and take part in operationalization of valuable insights from the data into business and digital applications.
Partner with internal/external stakeholders, product owners and team members and drive product development plans
Drive methodological innovations into data science and digital products in the different functional areas such as services, product development, supply chain, operations optimization, and similar domains
We believe you have
In this role as Data Scientist, you need to have with a good balance in these three different profiles:

Technical:
Strong coding skills in Python. Ability to write efficient code for deployment.
Experience developing deployment ready code with focus on robustness and efficient deployment.
Experience with R, C, Java or functional programming are meriting.
Experience building optimization automation for food processing industry.
Experience in neural network techniques for time series and image analysis and natural language processing are meriting.


Statistics & Mathematics: Knowledge of quantitative methods is important. From statistical inference to predictive and prescriptive modelling together with optimization skills. You have a strong algorithmic thinking and independent research ability.
Proven skills in multi-objective optimization applied to operations.
Experience with evolutionary computing for optimization.
Experience with fuzzy logic for modelling of uncertainty.
Analyse data with statistical rigor. Ensure accurate interpretation by combining business acumen with detailed data knowledge and statistical expertise. Ability for summarizing and explaining results focusing on the important information.
Build statistical models to uncover insights or effect changes and provides solutions to business problems.
Knowledge about common statistical models and machine learning models, i.e. understands what is going on “underneath the hood


Functional: Good understanding of operational processes, KPI’s and decision supporting systems. Mainly in areas like production, quality, maintenance, logistics and after-sales process (warranty). Complementary revenue management for pricing and marketing (customer insights).
Translate analytic insights into concrete, actionable recommendations for business or product improvement, and communicate these findings.
Drive efforts to enable independent interpretation of results through education, improved tools, and data visualization.
We Offer You
A variety of exciting challenges with ample opportunities for development and training in a truly global landscape
A culture that pioneers a spirit of innovation where our industry experts drive visible results
An equal opportunity employment experience that values diversity and inclusion
Market competitive compensation and benefits with flexible working arrangements

Apply Now
If you are inspired to be part of our promise to protect what’s good; for food, people, and the planet, apply through our careers page at https://jobs.tetrapak.com/.


This job posting expires on 2023-02-05
To know more about the position contact Pedro Corral at +46 46 36 1247
Questions about your application contact Susanne Stålring at +46 46 36 3919
For trade union information contact Sveriges Ingenjörer Lars Haraldsson at +46 46 36 2533 and Unionen Lisbeth Larsson at +46 46 36 2320

Title: Data Scientist - Stockholm, Solna
Description:
Are you passionate about machine learning and data analysis? Do you want to work in an international organization where your techniques will have a great impact on the business and customers? We are looking for a Data Scientist for the Process & System Development team who will be based in Solna.

At Arla, we strive to unlock the highest potential in each other while working together to create a sustainable future of dairy. We call it Stronger People Stronger Planet and it is deeply anchored in our organisation and founded on our commitment to respecting human rights, increasing access to healthy dairy nutrition, inspiring good food habits, and improving the environment for future generations. In order to succeed we need to hire people with a sustainable mindset.

About the job
As a Data Scientist at Arla you will be part of the Process & System Development team where you work together to develop processes and systems and identify new development areas with the focus on digital services. This can be services that supports our customers with information or services about purchases and deliveries of our products.

You will be a part of our function who works with Big Data, BI and AI with focus on analysis and predictive analysis. The role include a responsibility to identify and implement new technology to further develop our digital services and also analys and visualise data insights. You will be a part of the whole process, from the first idea to finished product.

The role as Data Scientist also include:
Collaborating with colleagues, customers and suppliers to gain knowledge about business issues
Analys data to identify new development areas and new solutions
Design and develop models with machine learning and optimizing techniques
Exchange knowledge with different markets within Arla through our Globala Data Science Community

Who are you?
We are looking for someone who is driven and wants to start their working career at Arla, we believe that you are newly graduated from the univeristy or have previous experience within Data Science. You have programming skills and enjoy analysing Big Data, you would also like to learn more about data bases and their structure. It is important that you are structured and methodical, and can explain complicated technical things in a pedagogical way in the dialogue with others.

In order to be successful in this role we believe that you have:
Experience of a tool box for machine learning/deep learning
Experience of programming, Python and/or R
The ability to identify solutions through data analysis
The ability to design and develop models with machine learning and optimizing techniques
An analytical ability to understand business issues
Fluent in English, both written and oral

It is meritorious if you have:
Experience in presentation tools such as Power BI, Dundas BI or Tableau
Technical knowledge about data bases and cloud technology such as Databricks or Azure
An interest in modelling and data pipelines
Previously worked with agile development techniques
Knowledge in Swedish writing/speaking

What do we offer?
We’re committed to professional development and promoting from within. Our positive and collaborative culture will bring out the best in you. And you’ll join a market leader who produces nutritious household favorite brands in a way that make things better for our customers, the farmers who own us, and the whole world.

Create the future – Grow with Arla

Application and contact
Please apply as soon as possible but no later than 2023.02.11. We process applications on a continuous basis and close the job opening once the right candidate has been found. Finding the right candidate is of high importance and for this, we can be flexible on the starting date. For additional information, please contact Thomas Peterson, Team Manager, arthpet@arlafoods.com.

At Arla Foods we want to create the conditions for our colleagues to have a sustainable work life by offering flexibility and the opportunity to work in the office, which is seen as the first choice, and remotely; based on the needs of the business and the employees. We call it the “Power of the Mix”.

Arla Foods is bound by collective agreements. At Arla we always make sure to offer good and competitive working conditions.

We have a purpose for Good
At Arla, we strive to unlock the highest potential in each other while working together to create a sustainable future of dairy. We call it Stronger People Stronger Planet and it is deeply anchored in our organisation and founded on our commitment to respecting human rights, increasing access to healthy dairy nutrition, inspiring good food habits, and improving the environment for future generations. In order to succeed we need to hire people with a sustainable mindset. Could this be you?

BEWARE! RECRUITMENT FRAUD
It has come to our attention that there are a number of fraudulent emails and fake recruitment campaigns on the internet from people purporting to work for Arla Foods. Learn more via this link.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Do you want to help improve the sleep and health of millions of people worldwide
Sleep Cycle is the best-rated sleep tracker out there and right now our Gothenburg office is growing. We are looking for a Data Scientist who wants to play a major role in a small and fast-growing company.
About the position
Sleep Cycle has millions of active users that every day generate massive amounts of data. In the role of Data Scientist at Sleep Cycle you enable the product and business owners to make data-driven decisions with an end-to-end responsibility for the data pipeline. This gives you the opportunity to work with the full data flow. In your role, you will focus on how to best utilize data by experimentation and data analysis in our quest of improving the product and ultimately help people sleep better.
Areas of responsibility
Enable the product and business owners to make data-driven decisions
Responsibility for the full data flow. Starting with the data ingestion, defining metrics, analyzing and modeling the data, and finally, the presentation of the data.
Utilize our data for experimentation and data analysis in our quest of improving the product and ultimately help people sleep better.
What is your background & experience?
Applying mathematical skills to real world heterogeneous data
Solid foundation in mathematical statistics and probability theory
Data driven approach to problem solving
Python, SQL, and general data visualization
Understanding the value of collaboration within teams
Ability to work independently with high quality, speed and commitment
M.Sc. or PhD in a relevant area with a solid foundation in mathematics.
5 + years of professional experience (counting PhD studies) in a data driven role working with high volume heterogeneous and structured data
Nice to have
Experience working with Google Cloud Platform, Looker, BigQuery, Amplitude, and Leanplum.
A/B testing on mobile platforms
Basic understanding of modern machine learning techniques
Location: Gothenburg

The Sleep Cycle app was launched in 2009 and is the most used intelligent sleep tracker in the world. Sleep Cycle makes waking up easy by tracking sleep patterns and waking its user up in the lightest sleep phase while providing sleep quality insights in easy-to-read graphs.
As a result of a steady organic growth of product and team, Sleep Cycle has over 48 million downloads worldwide, with millions of active users and growing. It is rated as the best sleep tracker on the market.

In this recruitment we collaborate with Exectech.

Title: Data Scientist – Optimization
Description:
At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.
Are You up for a Challenge?
We are looking for highly motivated and creative problem solvers that can help us build the next generation of Optimizers.

We are now strengthening and expanding our Crew Pairing Optimization Team to take our world leading optimization solutions to the next generation. Our planning products are the leading solutions on the market and we relentlessly strive to make them better – always aiming to maximize customer value. The Pairing optimizer today is used to schedule approximately 400 000 persons for 70 airlines.

To succeed in building the next generation of solutions, we need a world class Data Scientist – Optimization who wants to join our agile teams consisting of some of the best developers in the world. As a member of our agile teams, you get to take full responsibility for the products we build. You and the team will collaborate with other teams, partners and our clients to make sure we continuously raise the bar. You will also have the possibility to continuously deepen your knowledge by attending conferences and study groups, or perhaps even becoming a teacher in our own Academy.
Are you passionate about building great software?
Our teams have a lot of fun and are known for their professional attitude and a warm team spirit. They are committed to building the best optimization products on the planet. We hope that you are a person who:
Wants to be a driving force in Optimization
Likes to solve mathematical problems, especially discrete optimization problems
Is passionate about building robust software that is easy to use and maintain
Always wants to grow and learn new things and has a growth mindset
Continuously wants to innovate and explore new technology such as e.g. Machine Learning
Do you want to join one of the largest companies in the World?
The Gothenburg office is located close to the Central Station and is responsible for most of the development of Jeppesen’s Crew and Fleet Planning Optimization products. With people from more than 30 different countries working at the office, we offer a great and inspiring work environment. We put considerable value in personality and want our colleagues to apply an ‘ownermentality’ to the work they do.
So, if you want to join one of the largest companies in the world, work with solving extremely complex problems that affect the operations of major airlines and millions of travelers around the globe – reach out to us and let’s take the first step towards your new career.
Position Responsibilities:
Leads cross-functional teams to determine, define and deploy complex predictive/prescriptive analytic solutions to meet business objectives. Evaluates business objectives and determines stakeholder needs. Chooses best fit methods, defines algorithms, validates and deploys models to achieve business results. Performs necessary data preparation and enhancements to models.

Basic Qualifications (Required Skills/Experience):
Today we use a variety of tools and technologies. To give you a flavour, we mainly do development in C++ and Python. We use Jenkins to keep track of our releases and pipelines. When we are not working with our own solvers, we use 3rd party solvers from FICO (Xpress) and Gurobi. Our products run on a Linux & Oracle environment and we are now exploring how modern cloud architecture can improve the customer experience.
3+ years’ experience from developing similar applications
Strong C++ skills with proven track record of industrial product development
Strong problem-solving skills
As an optimization expert we see a mentoring personality and a focus around building strength within the team as well as outside the team
Creates state of the art solutions
Ensures high quality, including maintainability, of individual and team deliveries
Drives Clean Code
Suggests new tools, IDEs, Techniques
Drives Continuous integrations and deployments
Practice a DevOps mindset and drives implementation of shorter feedback loops
Fluency in English language
Preferred Qualifications (Desired Skills/Experience):
Airline or Railway applications
Simulation packages
Statistical analysis
Machine learning
Python
MSc Degree
Join us if you want:
Professional skills development with our virtual learning tools and platforms (Digital Campus, LinkedIn Learning, Degreed, EdX, Enterprise Mentoring, Communities of Excellence & Practice)
To broaden your experience in international projects, technical workshops and hackathons
Additional days off for Christmas break (December 24th-January 1st)
Employee recognition program (Boeing PridePoints)
Private Medical Insurance (Skandia)
Pension Plan (Defined Contribution Plan)
Employer is willing to sponsor applicants for employment visa status.
Please apply by sending your CV in English.

Relocation:
This position does not offer relocation sponsoring.
At the highest level, diversity and inclusion are part of Boeing's values. Having diverse employees, business partners and community relationships is vital to creating advanced aerospace and defense products and services for our diverse customers around the world. The company's commitment to diversity means providing a work environment for all employees that is welcoming, respectful and engaging, with opportunities for personal and professional development.

Export Control Requirements: Not an export control position

Equal Opportunity Employer:
We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not accept unlawful discrimination in our recruitment or employment practices on any grounds including but not limited to; color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, physical or mental disability, genetic factors, military and veteran status, or other characteristics covered by applicable law.
We have teams in more than 65 countries, and each person plays a role in helping us become one of the world’s most innovative, diverse and inclusive companies. Applicants are encouraged to share with our recruitment team any accommodations required during the recruitment process.

Title: Data Scientist/MLOps Engineer – Lund
Description:
Data Scientist/MLOps Engineer – Lund
Veritaz is a fast-growing IT-consultant firm. Our company is made up of insanely bright people from over 4 countries, and we are in Sweden, UK, US and Pakistan. The voyage has been incredible this far, but it is only the beginning.
Assignment Description:
We are currently seeking a highly skilled Data Scientist/MLOps Engineer to implement automated machine learning (ML) models for data prediction. The ideal candidate will have experience with Azure MLOps and be able to provide best practice setup and training along the way. The goal is to have a proof of concept (PoC) ready by the end of March and full implementation completed before the summer.
The candidate will be a senior-level professional, with a proven track record of delivering successful projects. The role will require a combination of data science, machine learning, and MLOps engineering skills. This is a great opportunity for an experienced data scientist/MLOps engineer to work on cutting-edge technology and drive the success of a high-impact project. If you meet the requirements below and are excited about this opportunity, please apply.
What you'll do:
· Design and implement automated ML models for data prediction
· Provide best practice setup for Azure MLOps
· Provide training and guidance to team members
· Communicate effectively with cross-functional teams
· Drive the project from start to finish, ensuring successful delivery
Who you are:
· Senior-level professional with a minimum of 5 years of experience
· Strong experience with Azure Machine Learning
· Excellent communication and process-driving skills
· Ability to work in Lund
Location: Lund
Job Type: Full-time
Ability to commute/relocate:
Stockholm: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Preferred)
Application Question(s):
What is your salary expectations?
When will you be available to join?
Do you need a sponsor with a Swedish working permit?
What is your level of proficient in Swedish?
Work authorization:
Sweden (Preferred)

Title: Data Scientist som vill skapa framtida historia
Description:
Hej!

Vilken framtida historia vill du skapa?
Vi på Artificial Collective
vill skapa framtida historia med AI och förbättra vardagen för miljarder människor, varelser och vår planet inom det kommande decenniet!

Det är vår vision, och den är stor!

Men vi är på god väg då vi idag samarbetar med några av Nordens mest spännande företag där vi tillsammans med de mest passionerade inom AI/Data, inspirerar vi varandra varje dag och riktar vår samlade kunskap mot att skapa de bästa AI-lösningarna som bidrar med en större nytta.
Bli en del av teamet ‍‍
som idag består av seniora konsulter inom Data Science och Machine Learning. För att fortsätta arbeta med de mest spännande projekten, söker vi just nu efter vår nästa kollega inom Data Science.

Som anställd eller egen konsult hos Artificial Collective får du möjligheten att arbeta med just det ditt hjärta bultar extra för. Både i individuella och i teamprojekt.

Du själv bestämmer över din tid, ersättning, vad du vill arbeta med och i vilken riktning du vill utvecklas. Istället för en gammeldags hierarki med konsultchefer, får du som en del av Artificial Collective, en dedikerad agent som tillsammans med dig ser till att du kommer dit! Exempelvis genom utbildning, inspiration eller med hjälp av mentorskap från en expert inom önskat område.

Vi söker inte enbart efter någon som har rätt teknisk bakgrund, utan någon som vill vara med och fortsätta forma Artificial Collective till det bästa möjliga, med och för oss alla.


Vi tror att du brinner för

Använda olika metoder för att hantera data, saknad data, obalanserad data, felaktig data, extremvärden osv.
Förstå, assistera och förbättra den befintliga processen för att underhålla och utöka data.
Formulera och strukturera problem för att hitta och kommunicera en väg framåt.
Analysera och visualisera komplexa data för att hitta nya mönster och insikter som kommer förbättra verksamheten och upplevelsen.
Bygga och producera AI-lösningar med olika ML-tekniker.
Programmera i lämpligt språk så som Python och SQL.

Vårt löfte
är att ge dig vad du behöver för att du ska kunna lägga mer tid på det som ditt hjärta bultar extra för!
Vi tror på frihet och att det skapar välmående vilket vi ser som avgörande för passion samt geniala idéer.
Vi tror på passion och att det är viktigt för glädje och fortsatt lärande. Vi vill frigöra din passion.
‍‍ Vi tror på styrkan i att arbeta tillsammans och rikta vår kollektiva passion mot visionära idéer och skapa bättre lösningar.
Samtidigt får du det bästa paketet av förmåner.
Lön: 40-80k/månad
Semester: 30-60 betalda dagar
Pension: Ja
Försäkringar: Ja
Friskvård: Ja
Visst låter det intressant?
Sök direkt och var med och skapa den framtida historian du vill se när vi tillsammans tar nästa stora steg inom AI!

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Who we are
Monto, part of Fortnox, is now looking for a Data Scientist!
Monto is on a mission to ensure that all small and medium sized businesses (SMEs) are able to access financing on fair terms. We want to level the playing field between SMEs and Enterprises by helping lenders become better at serving their SME customers. By leveling up lenders, helping them make use of real time accounting and financial data we will help them to help SMEs and thereby close the financing gap in the market. We are boosting the business of SMEs which will fuel the economy!
We are looking to hire great people, who are passionate about using their talents to generate success. We are currently looking for a Data Scientist to better understand, segment and predict customer’s behavior and their financial states.
Who you are
We are looking for ambitious people with a sense of ownership and responsibility. We need problem solvers, initiative takers, people that see opportunities and potential to improve. You will play an important role in taking Monto to the next level - thus, you should desire to go above and beyond to deliver and grow as an individual. At Monto we embrace change, you should dare to challenge the status quo and be persistent in doing so.
Moreover we believe that you are passionate about data science and want to be a part of Monto Data Science helping companies get access to financing based on their true real time behavior and financial data.
You have:
Knowledge of machine learning and statistics
Python and SQL programming skills
Experience developing ML models.
Strong communication skills and the ability to connect the findings to our business
Experienced with AWS is a plus
What’s in it for you?
You will be working in a multicultural team with other data scientists and ML engineers, creating machine learning solutions to add intelligence and automation to Monto’s SaaS platform. Our team owns our products end-to-end, including generating, extracting and preprocessing data, as well as developing, deploying, and monitoring our models.
Specifically you will:
Design, develop, and monitor next-gen ML solutions
Translate business and data needs to technical requirements, then work with other teams to ensure correct implementation
Work closely with product designers and developers to scope and design our products and identify potential new opportunities
Contribute to the team with your mathematical skills and modeling abilities
If you share our passion, join us in making the world a better place for small and medium businesses!
About Monto & Fortnox:
Monto is part of Fortnox AB (publ), a business platform that connects people, companies and organizations. We help companies start, grow and develop. With smart technical products, solutions and services, and the opportunity to connect them with hundreds of external parties, we are a hub for businesses in Sweden. Our vision is to create a prosperous society shaped by successful companies. Fortnox was founded in 2001 and has headquarters in Växjö and offices in Malmö, Linköping and Stockholm. The share is listed on Nasdaq Stockholm. For further information see www.fortnox.se

Are you curious about Monto's story? Read more about us here.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Role Description
Be driven by a customer value mindset and conduct data science practices with an end-to-end perspective: business understanding, iterative exploration, agile development, operationalization, monitoring, and continuous improvement.
Interpreting data and perform Data mining techniques focused on energy efficiency.
Apply Data Science in arriving at insights and use efficient visualization tools for communication
In depth analysis of fleet and Demo vehicles around the world to make the vehicles more efficient.
Required Skills
MS/M.Tech/M.E in Mathematics, Physics, IT or applicable engineering field
Experience in application of Data Science
Proven skills in data mining, data preparation and data analysis
Expertise in Data Visualization with Insights using Power BI, QlikView, etc.
Expertise in managing/programming data through SQL, Python, Azure, Hadoop, etc.
System thinking approach in problem solving
Job Type: Full-time
Salary: 520.00kr per day

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
We are looking for a Sr Data Scientist to join or consulting company located in Sweden. You will carry out evaluative and exploratory data analysis to generate insights useful for product and strategy decisions, and you will be able to communicate these insights in a clear way for non-technical stakeholders.

About the role
As a Data Scientist, you understand solutions in an overall perspective. Your specialty is to work closely with stakeholders across the organisation to define complex business problems and suggest the right analytical and technical solutions. Overall you are passionate about developing and implementing advanced models using state-of-the-art data technologies.

Required skills:
At least 3 years of working experience in a data scientist role or similar.
Deep understanding and professional experience working with advanced analytics, machine learning and statistics, developing and implementing models.
Proficiency in programming languages such as Python, R, Spark or similar technologies with associated machine learning libraries.
Strong analytical and creative mindset and problem-solving skills.
Ability to write efficient queries using SQL language.
Experience working in with multiple stakeholders in agile project methods such as SCRUM, Kanban or similar.
Cloud platform experience such as AWS or GCP.
Significant experience working with a large datasets ecosystems.
Data visualization tools and technologies such as Power BI, Tableau, Looker etc. are a plus.
A/B testing and marketing analytics experience is also a plus.
Excellent communication skills in English.
Ability to adapt to a dynamic work environment and make independent decisions.
Above all, you are curious, responsible, flexible, and aspiring to develop innovative products and services.
Perks and Benefits
Competitive Salary
Pension plan
Health and other insurance
Gym, sports & health benefit
Yearly conferences (often abroad)
Full relocation support (work permit fast track, flight ticket, help with finding apartment/housing, bank account, Swedish SSN etc)
Hybrid/remote work
About Recommit:
We have three key words - Care, Share and Commit - something that defines how we are in our daily work, in the meeting with our customers and towards each other
Recommit offers a foundation for our co-workers to enhance their technical skills within IT. We strongly believe in knowledge sharing and are always passionate to learn from each other
Our employees consist of senior technology developers as well as young talents that disrupt with new ideas for innovations and opportunities. We know that the best teams consist of a mixed group of individuals
We endorse cultural diversity and have long experience in relocating new coworkers to our company and country. Recommit is certified by the Swedish Migration Agency and we can in short period of time handle the process of a valid work permit. We also try to help as much as possible in all aspects when in come to integrate to Sweden and the Swedish society .


Recommit AB was founded in 2010 and our office is located in central Stockholm
Application:
Does this sound like something for you? Apply today and meet us for a first Teams meeting. If you have any questions, please contact our consultant manager Jonas Falkowski Källman at jonas.kallman@recommit.se, or +46733113114
We are looking forward to your application!

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
What is this about?
Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions. We understand how Computer Vision and AI can benefit the society. We stand ready to use our expertise to facilitate businesses in their journey into the era of AI. We work with several clients with various industry fields in close collaboration with top universities in Sweden.

Synteda is actively working on several unique products and solutions in various fields. Dream-innovate-create is our work process were our ideas go through different stages. We create successful solutions by checking feasibility of our product idea (POC) and develop our solution working with agile methodologies until we reach a complete full-scale product.

Synteda has a core team of highly qualified experts that provide assessment to identify challenges and explore different ideas to enhance effectiveness and develop specific algorithms to overcome company challenges. Synteda is built on ethical awareness, curiosity, transparency, respect, participation and last but not least science.

Synteda is growing rapidly and we are looking for a talented data scientist to join our team of experts.
What are we looking for?
Responsibilities
Work on our various platforms and customer assignments.
Collaborate with data scientists and help them test and develop new algorithms.
Enhance existing applications and platforms.
Research, build and implement new solutions.
Build and analyze new data models.
Application of optimization techniques to previous projects.
Analyze multi-variable data sets.
Adopt best practices and share them across the team.

Skills
Bachelor’s, Master’s, or Ph.D. degree in computer science or similar.
Programming experience in combination of Python, C#, C/C++, Spark, Java/Scala.
Knowledge of scientific computing language such as Matlab or R.
Exposure to big data platforms such as AWS, Azure, Hadoop.
Good knowledge of relevant data science packages such as Numpy, PyTorch, Tensorflow, Scipy, Pandas and basic mathematical modelling.
Experience in big data tools such as ElasticSearch/Soir and Kafka.
Experience creating ETL/ELT processes.
Experience with Databricks and Azure tools.
Knowledge of AI and machine learning models.
Good understanding of data engineering practices and data modelling.
Solid experience in multi-variable analysis.
You have experience working with large data sets and distributed computing tools.
Previous experience building machine learning models and data visualization.
Experience of agile development methodologies.
Fluent in English, both spoken and written is required.
Advantage with Swedish.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Vi startade Signific för att kunna lösa världens mest spännande och utmanande problem. Det gör vi genom att hjälpa organisationer och team att samla in, strukturera upp och agera på insikter från stora mängder kvantitativ data. På så sätt lär de sig snabbare om hur nytta, förändring och effekt skapas.
Signific jobbar med datadrivna, vassa och nyfikna kunder som t.ex. Detectify, Transfer Galaxy, M och SVT.
Som Data Scientist-konsult på Signific hjälper du våra uppdragsgivare att ta sin data till nya, insiktsskapande nivåer. Din förståelse för både affärs- och datamodeller kombinerat med analys och kod är superviktig för ett datadrivet, lärande arbetssätt. På Signific får du använda dina skills på stora, inspirerande problem.
Utöver att göra skillnad i dina uppdrag är du en stor del av ett framåtlutat bolag som sätter våra anställda i fokus. Vi är ett litet, flexibelt bolag med stora ambitioner och vill ha med dig på resan dit.
Vad du kommer få göra
Vi tror på en öppen approach till lösningar på våra kunders utmaningar. Vi väljer lösning efter problem och inte vice versa. Din roll kan därför variera beroende på ditt intresse och kundernas problem.
Som Data Scientist hos oss ser vi dig troligen göra några av följande saker:
Först och främst hjälpa företag skapa mer nytta av sin data
Ta komplex data till modeller och analyser som löser viktiga verksamhets- och samhällsproblem
Analysera stora mängder användardata för att driva produkt- och designbeslut
Kommunicera insikter och rekommendationer
Ha en nyckelroll att förflytta team och organisationer mot ett datadrivet arbetssätt.
Få ta del av och bidra till kunskapsdelning och nyskapande kultur ihop med dina kollegor
Utvecklas åt det håll du vill
Vem vi tror du är
Vi tror på att bygga ett bolag av olika personer som på olika sätt bidrar till att vi alla trivs och lyckas. För att du ska trivas hos oss och i din roll tror vi dock att det finns några saker som du checkar av merparten av:
Som person
Ser positivt på utmaningar
Gillar att vara självgående men också att samarbeta
Nyfiken på nya teknologier och problem
Vill vara så bra som möjligt på det du gör
Gillar att sälja, kunskapsdela och/eller bidra till kulturen bland dina kollegor
I din roll
Är genuint intresserad av att lösa kunders verksamhetsproblem
Har minst tre års arbetslivserfarenhet inom rollen eller liknande roller
Känner dig bekväm inom minst ett programmeringsspråk (t.ex. Python/Pandas, R eller SQL)
Har koll på visualiseringsverktyg (som t.ex. Tableau, Google Analytics, Google Data Studio)
Förstår vilka mått och mätetal som är viktiga för digitala produkter
Gillar och förstår statistik (som t.ex. A/B-tester, signfikanstester och regressionsmodellering)
Noggrann men också lösningsorienterad
Trivs att jobba i agila team och kanske också i en mer ledande roll.
Har stort intresse för Data Engineering/Science/Analytics i allmänhet
Högskoleutbildning är inget krav, men konkret arbetslivserfarenhet är det.
En spännande resa där du får vara med och påverka
Vi är ett nystartat litet bolag, med ambitioner att göra stort avtryck i våra uppdrag och på längre sikt. Vi vill skapa en samling av dom bästa inom vår nisch och bygga en stark kultur av gemenskap, ambition och kunskap. Något som gör en signifikant skillnad helt enkelt.
Hos oss får du
Utmanande uppdrag inom områden du är intresserad av
Kollegor som ser möjligheter och värdet med din kunskap inom data
Vassa kollegor som gillar att lära och läras av varandra
Konkurrenskraftiga förmåner
Inkluderande och hållbar arbetsmiljö
Vill du vara med och göra skillnad?

Title: Senior Full Stack Developer - Tech Lead
Description:
Description

How’d you like to work with an international team of passionate developers and an inspired sales team to help locals and travelers get personalised recommendations of places to see, things to do and events to attend in a city? Sounds interesting? Keep reading!

Cruncho is looking for an experienced Full Stack Developer with a backend orientation and some team leading experience, confident with the full cycle of front- and backend development. You’ll be joining a tight-knit, distributed tech team of a CTO/Backend Developer, 3 Full Stack Developers and a UI/UX Designer, working closely with the CEO and the Business Development team in shaping the development of our in-house products. In such an environment, your direct impact on Cruncho’s success and your own career is apparent.

Roles & Responsibilities

Development planning in collaboration with the tech team
Building new features from static designs (or, sometimes, just simple requirements)
Working with databases and real production data (querying, extracting reports, bulk updates, Postgres, MongoDB, Elastic Search, etc…)
Continuous development and maintenance of Cruncho’s frontend and backend apps - including a city guide, an event calendar, a quiz and a CMS.
Maintaining a consumer-focused outlook and aiding in the delivery of projects to market
Acting as a mentor to team members
Staying on top of technology trends and developments
Ensuring all technology practices adhere to regulatory standards
Shared responsibility of the product as a whole
Basic Qualifications

Masters degree in computer science or related field
A minimum of 3 years working in a technological role
A minimum of 6 month managerial experience
Advanced technological skillset and a demonstrated history with technology
Experience with responsive web UI
Experience with React, React Native, HTML & CSS (SASS)
Experience with relational and document databases
Experience with ExpressJS and TypeScript
Familiarity using Scrum/Agile development methodologies
Exceptional team management skills
Excellent verbal and written communication
Extensive industry knowledge with an eye towards the future
As a person, you are a proactive self-starter, able to work with a high level of independence while being a part of and mentoring a team. You are organised, well-structured and have an eye for details. You thrive in challenging environments, enjoy learning by doing and exhibit a drive for continuous improvement.

Additionally, you are enthusiastic about traveling and learning about new cultures. You’re optimistic, have a healthy sense of humour, and you know how to genuinely build trust and long-term relationships.

Finally, you are highly proficient in both spoken and written English.

Optional/Preferred Qualifications

Familiarity with the start-up environment
Experience with web scraping
Google Analytics, Matomo (or other analytics platforms)
HTML emails
Redux
Basic UI/UX design
Image editing software (e.g. Photoshop, Figma, Sketch, etc)
Some knowledge and/or experience of AI / Machine Learning.
Additionally, proficiency in additional language(s) is appreciated.

Perks

Being part of a growing business in an exciting market
Beautiful office in city-centre offering a flexible co-working space, free breakfasts, yoga sessions, afterworks...
Flexible working hours
Positions offered: 1

Ideal start: Nov/Dec 2022

Employment: fulltime

Salary: level to be discussed depending on seniority. Stock option program.

Location: Odenplan, Stockholm’s city-centre, Sweden. Company private office part of a co-working space providing us with a flexible work environment.

For more information, please visit cruncho.com

If you’re still reading this, why not drop us a line ? Attach your CV, a few lines about yourself and why you’d like to work with us. The sooner the better - recruitment is ongoing!

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Global companies and governmental entities rely on us to solve their most complex data challenges. Our employees collaborate to reduce risks and create opportunities for customers in more than 100 countries. We’re adaptable, curious and ambitious. That’s why here, you’ll have the freedom to drive change, the trust to find your own path, and the space to explore more.
Machine Learning Engineer/Data Scientist
From our research and engineering teams in Sweden and Germany to our sales, business and marketing offices around the world, BehavioSec is committed to making a better, more secure internet. Our company is always looking for enthusiastic, committed and smart people. As a member of our team, you’ll be contributing to a total rethink of how companies secure experiences for customers and users around the world to reduce fraud.
THE PROBLEMS
BehavioSec power real-time analyzing of behavioral data for Fraud prevention and authentication. We analyze data collected from the user and validates it against a stored profile for that user and calculates a risk of fraudulent usage for the session.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Work with a team with different backgrounds to frame problems, both mathematically and business wise.
Perform exploratory data analysis to gain a deeper understanding of the problem.
Construct and fit statistical, machine learning, or optimization models
Write production modeling code; collaborate with Software Engineers to implement algorithms in production
Analyze and Visualize findings and data to further enhance the product.
EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS
M.S. or Ph.D. in Statistics, Operations Research, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering Physics or another quantitative field.
Passion for solving unstructured and non-standard mathematical problems.
End-to-end experience with data, including querying, aggregation, analysis, and visualization.
Proficiency with Python Java or other programming languages.
Willingness to collaborate and communicate with others to solve a problem.
BEING A PART OF THE BEHAVIOSEC TEAM
Have Impact: We take on meaningful and challenging projects that affect fraud prevention on a global scale.
Collaborate: We work internally with people from a variety of backgrounds — such as product teams, engineering teams, sales teams. We also work externally with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.
Have Independence: We trust each other to effectively manage time and priorities—we don’t micromanage. We want to give people the space to think for themselves.
Grow: We push ourselves and our peers to improve themselves and the world around them.

Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
Här är en möjlighet att arbeta med det fullständiga dataflödet i en pipeline. I denna roll kommer du att fokusera på hur du bäst utnyttjar data genom experiment och dataanalys för att förbättra produkterna och i slutändan hjälpa våra kunder att bli mer konkurrenskraftiga på sin marknad.
Ansvarsområden
Du gör det möjligt för Semcons kunder att fatta datadrivna beslut
Du ansvarar för hela dataflödet. Från att välja och ange korrekta data, inklusive frågeställningar, därefter aggregering och bearbetning, definiera mått, analysera och modellera data och slutligen hur man visualiserar datan på bästa möjliga sätt.
Använda insamlade data för experiment och ytterligare dataanalys för framtida forskning.
Vad har du för bakgrund & erfarenhet?
Solid grund i matematisk statistik och sannolikhetsteori
Datadrivet förhållningssätt till problemlösning
Passion för att lösa ostrukturerade och icke-standardiserade matematiska problem
Tillämpat matematiska färdigheter på verkliga heterogena data
End-to-end-upplevelse med data
SQL, Python och allmän datavisualisering
Kunskaper i Java eller andra programmeringsspråk.
Förmåga att arbeta självständigt med hög kvalitet, snabbhet och engagemang
M.S. eller Ph.D. i statistik, operationsforskning, matematik, datavetenskap, teknisk fysik eller annat kvantitativt område.
5 + års yrkeserfarenhet i en datadriven roll som arbetar med stora icke-strukturerade data
Du är samarbetsinriktad, ödmjuk och mycket kommunikativ eftersom vi arbetar externt med våra kunder, ofta på plats, för att förstå och lösa deras problem.
Grundläggande förståelse för moderna maskininlärningstekniker
Gärna svenska, både i tal och skrift
Erfarenhet av att arbeta med ett team med olika bakgrund för att rama in problem, både matematiskt och affärsmässigt.
Plats:
Göteborg, på vårt kontor eller hos kund.
Om detta passar in på dig, tveka inte att skicka in din ansökan!
Om du har frågor kring tjänsten så är du välkommen att höra av dig till Magnus Svensson, Team Manager.
Magnus.svensson@semcon.com
Till bemannings-, förmedlings- och rekryteringsföretag och till dig som är försäljare:
Vi undanber vänligen men bestämt direktkontakt med bemannings-, förmedlings- och rekryteringsföretag samt andra externa aktörer och försäljare av ytterligare jobbannonser.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Om ten10
Hos ten10 kommer du ingå i en organisation som strävar efter ten10 värdesätter den personliga relationen och där varje individ får vara med att påverka både sin egen men även ten10s utveckling.
Vi tror på att bygga ett bolag av olika personer som på olika sätt bidrar till att vi alla trivs och lyckas. Utöver att göra skillnad i dem uppdrag vi gemensamt finner av intresse för dig och din utveckling så är du en stor del av ett framåtlutat bolag som där vi sätter våra anställda i fokus.
Hos oss ser man…
…positivt på utmaningar
…positivt på att samarbeta men klarar också av att vara självgående när det behövs
…positivt på nya teknologier och problem
…positivt på kompetensutveckling och bli bättre på det du arbetar inom
…positivt på att vara med och påverka

Att vara en konsult hos ten10
Vi vill ständigt bli bättre och är bara i uppstartsfasen av en spännande resa så vi vill därav ta in ytterligare en Data Scientist.
Som Data Scientist-konsult hos ten10 har du en nyckelroll i att demokratisera data ute på uppdrag. Genom vår gemensamma erfarenhet vet vi värdet av tillgänglig och stabil data och till vilken grund den kan ligga för framgångsrika och avgörande beslut.
I din roll som Data Scientist…
…har du vilja och intresse av att lösa kundernas problem och se det som en intressant utmaning
…har du minst tre års arbetslivserfarenhet inom rollen eller liknande roller
…känner du dig bekväm inom minst ett programmeringsspråk (t.ex. Python/Pandas, R eller SQL)

…har du koll på visualiseringsverktyg som exempelvis Tableau, Google Analytics, Google Data Studio)

…förstår du vilka mått och mätetal som är viktiga för digitala produkter

…gillar du och förstår statistik genom exempelvis A/B-tester, signfikanstester och regressionsmodellering

…har du erfarenhet av av big data-teknologier som Hadoop, Kafka, SQL, Spark m.m.
…är du noggrann men också lösningsorienterad
…trivs du att jobba i agila team

Vad får man ut av att vara en ten10are

Hos ten10 är det viktigt att finna en sund balans mellan privat- och arbetsliv. Vi arbetar därför alltid tillsammans för att finna vad som kan kan vara bra för din vardag. Vi erbjuder inte bara valmöjligheter hur du vill påverka din arbetsdag utan även i ersättningsmodeller. Vi erbjuder en av marknadens mest attraktiva lönemodeller och där du får kompensation för det värde du skapar.
När du är en del av ten10 är det viktigt att du även känner det och kan dela med dig av dina erfarenheter, tankar och ideér. Detta kan du göra när vi alla ses gemensamt och umgås på AWs, utlandsresor, julbord eller när vi gör något annat kul ihop.
Vi pratar inte bara om att vi faktiskt bryr oss om våra medarbetare utan hela vår verksamhet utgörs av våra medarbetare. Vår ambition är att skapa dem rätta förutsättningarna för just dig!

Title: Summer Internship, Data Science | Platform Mission (EMEA)
Description:
Students
The Platform team creates the technology that enables Spotify to learn quickly and scale easily, enabling rapid growth in our users and our business around the globe. Spanning many fields, we work to make the business work; creating the frameworks, capabilities and tools needed to welcome a billion customers. Join us and help to amplify productivity, quality and innovation across Spotify.
Location
Stockholm or Remote EMEA
Job type
Internship
We are looking for Data Scientist Interns to Join The Band and help drive a data-first culture across Spotify, with a focus on internal productivity. You will analyze internal networks within the Spotify organization to better understand how people at Spotify communicate and collaborate with each other.
What you'll do
Be a valued member of an autonomous, multi-functional agile team focusing on understanding and enabling developers’ productivity.
Collaborate with other data scientists, engineers, product managers, designers and user researchers to tackle exciting and challenging problems.
Be a member of the Spotify-wide data-science community.
Perform analyses on internal datasets to extract practical insights that will help drive decisions across the business.
Build dashboards and recurring reporting results, empowering creative growth and business decisions.
Communicate data-driven insights and recommendations to key collaborators.
Who you are
You are pursuing a Bachelor’s, Master’s degree, or bootcamp certification in Science, Computer Science, Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, or a similar quantitative subject area
You have a graduation date of 2023 or 2024.
You currently have valid work authorization to work in the country in which this role is based that will extend from June to August 2023.
You harbor a passion for numbers and the use of data to make decisions.
You have the technical competence to perform more analytics in one or more of the following areas:
Coding skills (such as Python or R).
Analytics tools experience (such as Pandas, SQL, or Tableau).
Experience performing data analysis.
Where you'll be
We are a distributed workforce enabling our band members to find a work mode that is best for them!
Where in the world? For this role, it can be within the EMEA region in which we have a work location.
Prefer an office to work from instead? Not a problem! We have plenty of options for your working preferences. Find more information about our Work From Anywhere options here.
Working hours? We operate within the Central European time zone for collaboration.
Our global benefits
Extensive learning opportunities, through our dedicated team, GreenHouse.
All The Feels, our employee assistance program and self-care hub.
Social events, everything from fikas and team outings to concerts, panels and talks.
Flexible public holidays, swap days off according to your values and beliefs.
Spotify Premium Account, listen without limits with a free employee account.
Swag, a Spotify welcome kit and official merch you can’t get anywhere else.
Learn about life at Spotify
Our paid summer internships last for 10-13 weeks and start at the beginning of June. The last day to apply is February 7th, 2023 at 10 AM CET.

Spotify is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome at Spotify for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what’s playing in your headphones. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all thrive, contribute, and be forward-thinking! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our differences that we will find the power to keep revolutionizing the way the world listens.

Spotify transformed music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the chance to enjoy and be passionate about these creators. Everything we do is driven by our love for music and podcasting. Today, we are the world’s most popular audio streaming subscription service.

Title: Data Scientist in Predictive Computational Chemistry and Machine Learning
Description:
Do you have expertise in, and passion for, deriving knowledge from data and computational modelling? Would you like to apply your expertise to implement transformative Artificial Intelligent and Machine Learning based methods to drive the digital transformation in a company that follows the science and turns ideas into life changing medicines? Then AstraZeneca might be of interest to you!
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are
empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
Pharmaceutical Sciences at AstraZeneca delivers the therapies of the future through scientific leadership in drug delivery, design of synthetic routes, and manufacturing of Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients and drug products. In essence, we are working “from molecule to medicine” to develop medicines for our patients today and tomorrow.
The Data Science and Modelling department within Pharmaceutical Sciences is developing a digital transformation strategy to drive innovation, optimization of the drug development process and data-driven decision making.
We now have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Scientist or Associate Principal Scientist, depending on your background and experience, in our Data Science – Substance team. This role can be based in either Gothenburg, Sweden or Macclesfield, United Kingdom.
What you’ll do
In this role you will get the opportunity to engage with key internal and external stakeholders to identify and validate impactful solutions to provide scientific leadership and drive innovation. You will work at the forefront of the digital transformation within AstraZeneca, turning ideas into life changing medicines for patients!
Typical responsibilities in this role
Use a combination of data driven models and molecular modelling to predict and elucidate chemical structures of impurities and degradants of pharmaceutical substances as well as formulated drug products.
Identify and utilize internal and external data sources and test, develop, and implement new combinations of machine learning and mechanistic modelling workflows to predict physical chemical properties and drug substance reactivity to be used by other scientists
Support drug project campaigns with expert insights on chemical reactivity, stability, and catalysis
Essential requirements
PhD in computational chemistry or equivalent experience
Track record of applying molecular modelling to druglike molecules
Proven experience of using machine learning to build predictive models
Skills and experience in modelling of chemical reactivity and analytical chemistry data
Good knowledge of Python programming including machine learning frameworks such as TensorFlow, Scikit-learn as well as cheminformatics packages such as, RDkit.
Knowledge of end-to-end software such as PipelinePilot, Knime or Dataiku is beneficial.
Excellent communication skills, written and spoken
Self-motivated
Team player
Why AstraZeneca
At AstraZeneca, we turn ideas into life changing medicines and strive to continuously meet the unmet needs of patients worldwide. Working here means being entrepreneurial, thinking big, and working together to make the impossible a reality. Ultimately, it’s more than a job. We know that our work impacts people with serious conditions, many of whom have no other alternatives. That’s what drives us – the potential to impact over one billion patients worldwide.
So, what’s next?

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
About Assessio
Assessio is one of the largest Talent Assessment suppliers in the Nordics as well as in the Netherlands. As a SaaS company, we provide our services through internally developed SaaS platforms. We are 140 dedicated co-workers who share our vision of Zero Talent Waste.
We strive to contribute to an effective and fair labor market where everyone is assessed based on equal, relevant terms. Where potential is valued, and organizations find the talent they need.
Besides joining us on our journey to achieve our vision #Zerotalentwaste, we also offer a competitive remuneration package that includes excellent benefits, such as competitive salaries, a generous wellness allowance of SEK 5000 / year, and 6 weeks of vacation. In addition, participation in a bonus scheme, and the opportunity to work both within our centrally located Stockholm office and remotely for employees within Sweden.
Job Description

Our SaaS platform team develop and maintain the SaaS platforms that help our clients recruit and develop their workforce. As a Data Scientist at Assessio you will design, implement, and deploy robust prediction algorithms that give our customers completely new and unique insights. You will collaborate closely both with product owners and the whole engineering team. Assessio’s SaaS platform team comprises talented individuals with a broad range of cultural backgrounds. Your contribution will be essential to both the team and the business success of Assessio group. We are thus looking for a team player with a strong sense of commitment and responsibility, as well as excellent problem-solving skills.
Main Responsibilities
Research, design, implement, deploy and operate robust and scalable prediction algorithms with the target to give our clients completely new and unique insights
Design and implement pipelines and services for pre-processing, training, and serving of machine learning models and algorithms.
Communicate with stakeholders to understand & refine the business needs and targeted outcomes.
Working closely for the agile teams developing our new SaaS platform
Contribute to the definition and implementation of best practices in terms of data infrastructure and deployment pipelines.
Qualifications
B.Sc degree or higher in relevant engineering / data science field
Proficiency in a relevant programming language (e.g. Python as well as SQL)
Minimum 4 years of hands-on work experience in the Data Science field, preferably working with a range of machine learning approaches and algorithms.
Good knowledge and understanding of common predictive machine learning approaches and related performance metrics.
Deep understanding of predictive modelling, clustering and classification methods and algorithms.
Excellent problem-solving skills.
Good communication skills.
Good English skills (speaking and writing).
Beneficial to have:
Knowledge of trade-offs and considerations related to the application of machine learning and algorithms in social and health sciences.
Experience from working with cloud-based systems, particularly AWS, and its machine learning services.
Interest in data mesh and decentralised data architectures.
M.Sc. degree in the data science field.
Reporting
The Data Scientist is reporting to the CTO
Next step
Does this sound like the right job for you? Send us your application today!
The first step in the process will be to complete two tests: a problem-solving test (Matrigma) and a personality test (MAP). It will take you approximately 30 minutes – and we guarantee valuable feedback after the assessments and a quick response from our side. You will find more info about the process at our Career Site.
We look forward to getting in touch!
If you have any questions regarding the recruitment process, please contact Lydia Nöjd
– lydia.nojd@assessio.se

Title: Data Insight Expert/Data Scientist in Pharmaceutical Sciences
Description:
We harness digital, data science & AI to fast-forward our research. Making sure work born in a lab can make a real difference. Everyday, impacting patients’ lives across the world.
What we do
AstraZeneca is a global, science-driven biopharmaceutical business and our innovative medicines are used by millions of patients worldwide. Ultimately, our aim is to work towards a cure for some of the world’s most complex diseases. Whether that’s by shaping the patient ecosystem and focusing on outcomes, or by progressing potential medicines and accelerating their launch.
Pharmaceutical Sciences at AstraZeneca delivers the therapies of the future through scientific leadership in drug delivery, design of synthetic routes, and manufacturing of Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients and drug products. In essence, we are working “from molecule to medicine” to develop medicines for our patients today and tomorrow.
The Data Science and Modelling department within Pharmaceutical Sciences is developing a digital transformation strategy to drive innovation, optimization of the drug development process and data-driven decision making.
We now have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Scientist or Associate Principal Scientist, depending on your background and experience in our data science Product team based in Gothenburg, Sweden.
What you’ll do
In this role, you will get the opportunity to engage with key internal and external stakeholders to identify and validate impactful solutions to provide scientific leadership and drive innovation. Our team interacts with many functions within the company such as chemistry, formulation work, drug delivery, analytical sciences and solid-state development meaning you will have a diverse set of interactions and impact possibilities. You will simply be at the forefront of the digital transformation within AstraZeneca, turning ideas into life changing medicines for patients!
Typical responsibilities in this role
Together with scientific experts develop a strategy to extract and capture data, perform analysis, and be able to use the information to support drug project development decisions.
Utilize Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to build predictive models to generate knowledge in a diverse set of drug development areas
Develop and implement proof-of-concept algorithms, models, workflows and visualizations to be used by other scientists
Act as a role model and mentor to scientists with less experience in machine learning and to champion FAIR data practices
Develop training material and provide training to AstraZeneca user groups
Plan, write and publish high quality scientific papers.
Essential requirements
PhD in computational chemistry, data science, informatics, physics or similar
Track record of applying knowledge graphs, text mining, and natural-language processing
Proven experience of using machine learning to build predictive models
Understanding of natural science, preferably in the field of chemistry or chemoinformatics
Strong record in Python programming including machine learning frameworks such as TensorFlow, Scikit-learn as well as cheminformatics packages such as, RDkit.
Knowledge of end-to-end software such as PipelinePilot, Knime or Dataiku is beneficial.
Excellent communication skills, written and spoken
Self-motivated
Team player
Why AstraZeneca
At AstraZeneca, we turn ideas into life changing medicines and strive to continuously meet the unmet needs of patients worldwide. Working here means being entrepreneurial, thinking big, and working together to make the impossible a reality. Ultimately, it’s more than a job. We know that our work impacts people with serious conditions, many of whom have no other alternatives. That’s what drives us – the potential to impact over one billion patients worldwide.
So, what’s next?
Are you already imagining yourself joining us? Good, because we can’t wait to hear from you! Welcome with your application; CV and cover letter, no later than February 27th, 2023.
