Title: Data Scientist Manager
Description:
We believe that our future success will be based on our ability to leverage the large amounts of data generated on our platform every day. We need the ability to gain fast insights from usage of our services to enable short cycles of product refinement and be able to develop new data-driven services based on all of our data.
During 2020 we began migrating our backend services to the Google Cloud Platform (GCP) with the ambition of being one of the few banks with cloud-based services in a highly regulated industry. During 2021 we started to build our next generation data & analytics environment on top of that and also on GCP.
This year we will focus more on personalisation and develop the capabilities we need to be able to use data-driven services to personalise the customer experience and contribute to other strategic goals.
About the role
As a Data Scientist Manager your focus will be to develop, implement and maintain different types of data-driven services together with other Data scientists and development teams, as well as lead Data scientists and Data analysts.
This role is part of Data & Insights at Nordnet, consisting of data engineering, business intelligence and data science competence responsible for the new environment, spanning from data pipelines to dashboards to data-driven services as well as data analysts supporting the organisation with insights in the daily work. The Data scientists and Data analysts are integrated in other development teams to ensure that we understand the customer needs and develop the best data-driven services and insights.
As Data Science Manager you are responsible for the outcome of your teams, and you use coaching, facilitation and your practical experience to help your teams grow, succeed and continuously deliver value. You are also responsible for hiring, staffing and onboarding.
About you
You are passionate about data, leadership and want to contribute with your experience and knowledge when we take our next steps in developing data-services and supporting the organisation with insights.
As a Data Scientist Manager we believe that this is you
Experience from Machine Learning frameworks and developing end-to-end projects in production.
Experience from working in GCP
Strong communication skills and have the ability to engage both technical and non-technical stakeholders in our vision
An empathic leader, willing to share your knowledge and mentoring and coaching others.
Experience of driving change in an organisation
Good understanding of data engineering practices and data modelling
Bank and Finance experience
Hold a BA degree or equivalent in engineering, computational or technical subject.
What we offer
Nordnet started from a passionate belief that changing the hierarchical financial world was possible. We became part of redefining the industry when we gave the customers power over their own savings. You will become part of a journey that has only yet started towards the vision of making our customers the best investors they can be. To be leading in IT is pivotal for that journey and you will work with colleagues who have a great passion for that goal.
We are 800 employees in Stockholm, Oslo, Helsinki and Copenhagen. We cooperate, exchange ideas and use our core competencies in order to continuously improve the way we meet our customers. Open communication, creativity and engagement are important parts of our everyday life at the office.
Visit us on www.nordnetab.com,www.nordnet.se,
www.nordnet.no, www.nordnet.dk_ and _www.nordnet.fi.
Application
We will start interviewing immediately. Please note that we do only accept applications through our recruitment system, hence no email applications will be considered.
If you have questions, please contact Talent Acqusition Partner Alva Hellberg at alva.hellberg@nordnet.se
We want to inform you that Nordnet conducts credit and background checks on the final candidate.
We look forward to receiving your application!
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Founded in 2018, Kreditz is already the market leader in PSD2-credit scoring products.
We use Open Banking/PSD2-technology to create our revolutionizing real-time credit scoring products, which are beloved by banks, financial institutions, iGaming companies and many more. Kreditz products enable consumers, and businesses, to gain financial inclusion, and financial opportunity where none would be available with traditional credit scoring systems.
Our long-term vision "One world, One score" translates into our everyday mission of financial inclusion, and financial opportunity, for everyone around the globe
– Everyone deserves a fair assessment.
Come join us on our impactful mission!

ABOUT THE POSITION
Thanks to 18 months of unbroken growth (+310% FY21 vs FY20) we are now looking to increase our analytics organization further with an awesome Data Science ‘magician’ eager to advance Kreditz revolutionizing products even further alongside a team of credit scoring experts, mathematicians and genuinely passionate colleagues.
We are currently entering an exciting phase (startup>scaleup) where we will expand our market presence further, from the Nordics to selected countries in Europe. Our clients range from some of Europe’s largest banks and iGaming companies to smaller, innovative businesses.
As a Data Scientist at Kreditz, your playing field is data, vast amount of data. Our products and services are highly data driven, and to remain innovative you need to be confident in the analysis of both the known, and the unknown. Kreditz expects you to be able to analyze large internal and external data sets, make data driven conclusions, and evaluate your findings to optimize Kreditz algorithms and statistical models. This role is an important part of Kreditz growing analytics team, which is led by our CAO.
If you share the excitement to work with state-of-the-art technology within Open Banking/PSD2, and to deliver market leading solutions that make a positive impact on our society, all the while being part of a growth journey across the world – this is the right position for you!

WHAT CAN KREDITZ OFFER
One-way ticket to an amazing growth journey you will never forget – A journey where everyone in the team plays a central role for our company’s success
Fun-loving, passionate, and talented colleagues with whom to share small and big, company and personal, milestones and accomplishments
Humble corporate culture – we celebrate all wins, no matter the size, together
24/7 access to gym/sauna/sports center at our office PLUS additional wellness allowance

TASKS
Some of the tasks you will be performing as Data Scientist at Kreditz:
Management and structuring of vast amounts of data
Analysis, interpretations and predictions of data
Transaction categorization and exploration (NLP, classification)
Optimization of Kreditz algorithms and statistical models
Model development, follow ups and evaluation
Advancement and implementation of DL and ML models
Project lead and participation for client projects
Proactive data driven product development together with Product owner

WE ARE LOOKING FOR
A colleague who is analytical, structured and communicative. Someone who (like us) is up for the BIG challenge to disrupt traditional credit scoring systems via Open Banking/PSD2-technology. To be successful in this role, you must have a positive
“We can do it” mindset, along with an appreciation of working in a fast-paced growth company. You are comfortable in being independent in your daily work as well as acting with responsibility both towards your colleagues and clients.
Additionally, we believe that you have:
+2 yrs experience from financial services/tech/insurance/consulting or equivalent relevant experience
A relevant academic background (Engineering, Data/IT, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics)
Some experience from DL/ML/NPL projects within relevant industry
Confident in coding languages such as: Python, R and SQL
Very good communications-, and presentation-, skills in English (speech/writing), Swedish or other language skills is meritorious
Credit risk modeling from bank or financial institutions is meritorious
Experience from PSD2/Open Banking is meritorious

APPOINTMENT OF ROLE
Q4 2022
SCOPE
Full time, permanent employment (tillsvidareanställning)
SALARY
Fixed monthly salary
REPORTING
You will be reporting to the company's CAO
WORKPLACE
Our office is in Danderyd, Stockholm.
RECRUITMENT PROCESS
We interview candidates on an ongoing basis (ongoing selection)

CONTACT
Lorenzo Puccio, COO, lorenzo@kreditz.com
If you want to know more about the role, feel free to reach out to Magnus Källhager, Chief Analytics Officer, magnus@kreditz.com , +4670-7913984

Title: Senior Full Stack Developer - Tech Lead

Description

How’d you like to work with an international team of passionate developers and an inspired sales team to help locals and travelers get personalised recommendations of places to see, things to do and events to attend in a city? Sounds interesting? Keep reading!

Cruncho is looking for an experienced Full Stack Developer with a backend orientation and some team leading experience, confident with the full cycle of front- and backend development. You’ll be joining a tight-knit, distributed tech team of a CTO/Backend Developer, 3 Full Stack Developers and a UI/UX Designer, working closely with the CEO and the Business Development team in shaping the development of our in-house products. In such an environment, your direct impact on Cruncho’s success and your own career is apparent.

Exceptional team management skills

You are organised, well-structured and have an eye for details. You thrive in challenging environments, enjoy learning by doing and exhibit a drive for continuous improvement.

Additionally, you are enthusiastic about traveling and learning about new cultures. You’re optimistic, have a healthy sense of humour, and you know how to genuinely build trust and long-term relationships.

HTML emails

Flexible working hours

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Technology | DataScientist | Stockholm, Sweden

Who we are

We are ferritico, a Swedish software company disrupting the global steel industry. Based on more than 10 years of world leading KTH research we are developing a machine learning tool provided to our customers as a SaaS. The ferritico service digitalizes the processes of developing, manufacturing and implementing steel, helping our customers to significantly cut time and costs.

We aggregate large sets of steel properties and process data and apply machine learning models enabling our customers to predict and view correlations in data when optimizing materials, products and processes. Ferritico is well funded through support from i.a. EIT and Vinnova although already generating revenues. Ferritico is used in production by two global steel companies and ferritico is currently strengthening the team with a Data Scientist as a consequence of increased service demand.

The Opportunity

This employment constitutes a unique opportunity to join the ferritico team in central Stockholm. As a Data Scientist you will be given a lot of responsibility and autonomy in developing our models and machine learning software. As we are still a small team, you will be given a unique opportunity to shape the digitalization of the steel industry by:

Managing and organizing the aggregation and cleaning of databases in collaboration with our materials engineers
Developing machine learning models and implement these with our software developers to optimize for our customers
Validating previously developed models as well as future models
Maintaining and monitoring models in production and support customers in performing model simulations

You are passionate

about developing result-focused and innovative machine learning solutions. You embrace new technology and the opportunity to contributeto and learn from related competence fields while taking responsibility for your deliverables.

Requirements:

Masters, PhD, or equivalent experience in a quantitative field (Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, Artificial Intelligence, etc.)
Experience with at least one programming language, preferably Python, and SQL databases.
Machine learning in R, scikit-learn and pandas libraries
Rigorous attention to detail and focus on quality of deliverables
Ambitious and independent self-learner with genuine interest for data, statistical modeling and machine learning software

Meriting skills:

Interest in or experience from materials engineering and especially the steel industry.
Basic understanding of front-end development frameworks, e.g. React and bootstrap.
Happy to communicate with customers, outline their processes and propose machine learning solutions
Git for version management.
Experience from using AWS hosting solutions.

Apply now

by sending us your resume to contact@ferritico.com. Add subject line “Data Scientist”.

Please contact Claes Holmström if you have any questions: +46 (0)8 121 530 05

Title: Data Scientist till Sesol!
Description:
Sesol levlar upp! Vi bygger nu upp vårt nya tech-team där vi nu söker dig med tidigare erfarenhet av Machine-learning, datastrukturer och algoritmer. Är du sugen på nya utmaningar inom Green-Tech? Välkommen in med din ansökan idag.

Vem är du?
Du är en analytisk dataexpert som har tekniska färdigheter för att lösa komplexa problem samt nyfikenheten att utforska vilka problem som behöver lösas, kunna bygga prediktiva modeller med hjälp av molnplattformar och lokala system. Du har mycket god kunskap om molntjänster och verktyg som förbättrar datautvinningen på ett effektivt sätt.
Du är van vid att lösa komplexa problem inom ämnena maskininlärning, datateknik och mjukvaruteknik.
Du har erfarenhet och ledarskap för att driva innovativa funktioner i applikationer.
Vad vi önskar av dig:
Du har minst 5-års branscherfarenheter som dataforskare eller maskininlärningsingenjör
Du har erfarenhet och goda kunskaper om Python och SQL/Non-SQL DB

Gedigen kunskap om datastrukturer och algoritmer
Du har tidigare erfarenhet som teknisk ledare och produktledare.
Du besitter en bra kommunikationsförmåga och erfarenhet av att arbeta med en dynamiska produkter.

Du har erfarenhet av att hantera projekt och distributioner med Jira och GitLab/Github (eller liknande)
Du har förståelse och erfarenhet av agil metodik
Du är en problemlösare som tänker på det bästa sättet att lösa uppgiften baserat på kravspecifikationen. Du gillar att utveckla på ett strukturerat sätt så att koden kan återanvändas. Du brinner för att utveckla hållbara lösningar och förstår vikten av teamarbete.

Vad erbjuder vi dig?
Stort ansvar och frihet i din roll
Möjligheten och förtroendet att bygga upp vår tech-avdelning i ett innovativt och expansivt bolag inom Green Tech
Golden League, ett program med fokus på din kompetensutveckling
Bra lön och bra förmåner
Chansen att jobba på ett innovativt bolag inom Green Tech.

Om Sesol AB
Vi är en trygg partner för dem som ska investera i solceller, elbilsladdare eller batterier.
Vi är idag över 700 medarbetare. Vårt huvudkontor ligger i Jönköping, vi har också etablerat oss i Kalmar, Helsingborg, södra Stockholm, Karlstad, Göteborg, Örebro, Norrköping, Uppsala.
Varje dag levererar vi anläggningar med högsta kundnöjdhet i fokus. Eftersom fler och fler får upp ögonen för solceller, elbilsladdare och batterier så innebär det att vi arbetar med anläggningar i alla storlekar, från en helt vanlig villa till stora parker. All vår personal är behörig och anställda direkt i Sesol vilket är viktigt för oss för att kunna leverera den kvalité vi står för som företag. Vi kan stolt säga att vi är en helhetsleverantör, på riktigt.

Om anställningen
Lön: Fast
Placering: Jönköping
Tillträde: Omgående eller enligt överenskommelse
Anställningsvillkor: Heltid

Välkommen in med din ansökan idag!
Har du frågor om tjänsten är du varmt välkommen att kontakta HR-teamet på Jobb@Sesol.se. OBS: Ansökan tas endast emot via vår hemsida.

Title: Data Scientist till AFRY X i Malmö
Description:
Företagsbeskrivning

AFRY är ett ledande europeiskt företag med global räckvidd inom teknik, design och rådgivning. Vi är 19 000 hängivna experter som skapar hållbara lösningar för kommande generationer. Som Data Scientist kommer du tillhöra AFRY X, vår division som erbjuder tjänster och rådgivning inom digitalisering, industriell Internet of Things (IoT), artificiell intelligens, design och cybersäkerhet. Med hjälp av digitalisering hjälper vi våra kunder att snabba på omställningen till ett mer hållbart samhälle. AFRY X South är i dagsläget ca 100 medarbetare med bred kompetens som täcker allt från mjukvaruutveckling till projektledning och test.
Som anställd hos oss erbjuds du:
Balans i arbetslivet
En tydlig onboarding-process för dig som nyanställd
Avsatt tid för kompetensutveckling på månadsbasis
Tillgång till ett stort utbud av aktiviteter genom Club AFRY som bland annat anordnar resor, träningstillfällen, fester med mera
Konkurrenskraftiga förmåner gällande pension, friskvård och föräldraledighet som regleras i vårt kollektivavtal
Företagsrabatter med externa partners genom vår förmånsportal Advantage You

Jobbeskrivning

Är du passionerad kring Machine Learning? Vet du din väg runt data?

På AFRY söker vi nu efter en erfaren Data Scientist. Du kommer vara del av ett litet team där hela livscykeln för Machine Learning är beaktad, från dataanalys till servern och skalning. Teamet levererar start-till-slut lösningar och hjälper ibland till under kortare delar av processen. Detta betyder att du kommer jobba med allt ifrån insamling av data till analys, rensning, förändring till att träna och leverera modeller.
Som en Data Scientist så kommer du ha större fokus på analys & förberedelse av data, inklusive:
Förstå affärsmål
Undersöka och visualisera data för djupare förståelse och därefter identifiera skillnader i datadistribution som kan påverka modellval i den verkliga världen
Verifiera datakvalité, alternativt skapa hög kvalité genom processering
Skapa features, förbereda och augmentera dat
Extract, Transform, Load (ETL)

Kvalifikationer
Har minst fem års erfarenhet av en liknande tjänst och kunskap inom branchens bibliotek/ramverk så som PyTorch eller Tensorflow
Har kunskap kring datastrukturer, modellering och mjukvaruarkitektur
Bor i Sverige och talar svenska, gärna nära Malmö då kontoret är i Malmö
Du bör också vara duktig på
Python
För att trivas i denna roll ser vi att du har en problemlösar-attityd och att du trivs att jobba i en föränderlig miljö där du interagerar med folk och grupper i projekt. Du skall genuint gilla att utforska nya tekniker och att ta dig framåt. Självfallet skall du ha ett starkt intresse i digitalisering!

Ytterligare information

Omfattning: Heltid, tillsvidare
Start: Enligt överenskommelse
Sista ansökningsdatum: 27 februari
Kontaktuppgifter vid frågor:
Hampus Londögård
Team Leader Future Technologies
hampus.londogard@afry.com

Stina Haugland
Recruitment Partner
stina.haugland@afry.com
AFRY is committed to creating an inclusive & diverse environment and we are actively looking for qualified candidates irrespective of gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, ethnicity, religion, disability, or age. You will be part of a global and diverse company where our differences are our strengths. Join us to accelerate the transition towards a sustainable society.

Title: Senior Data Scientist to Greenely
Description:
Greenely is on a mission to create the best customer experience for the modern energy consumer by using technology. We are a digital energy provider that helps people reduce their electricity costs by optimizing their home and car's electricity usage with smart technology in an app!
We are now looking for a Data Scientist who wants to be a part of our journey to make the world more sustainable and help consumers to reduce their energy usage!
The opportunity

We are looking for a Senior Data Scientist to help the company and the product grow. As a Senior Data Scientist, you will be responsible for analyzing large data sets and finding patterns to help Greenely's business achieve its goals.

Your challenge

Your daily work includes:
Identify valuable data sources
Analyze large amounts of information to discover trends and patterns
Build predictive models and machine-learning algorithms
Present information using data visualization techniques
Propose solutions and strategies to business challenges
Coordinate with different teams (ex., product development teams) to implement and monitor outcomes.

Team and workplace

You will be collaborating with the product teams to analyze data and build predictive models. You will also have the opportunity to help and be part of a growing team of data scientists.
Our office is located at Vasagatan 40 in central Stockholm and we apply a hybrid workplace solution.

About you

To be successful in this role, we believe you have proven experience as a Data Scientist or Data Analyst. You have excellent communication and presentation skills and you do also have:
Experience in SQL, Python, and R
Understanding of machine learning and operations research
Strong math skills
Experience with predictive modeling
Experience using business intelligence tools (Ex. Tableau)
Master’s or Ph.D. in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or similar fields

It is meritorious if you also have experience in other program languages and experience analyzing data from 3rd party providers such as Google, Facebook Insights, etc. We do also see it as a plus if you have experience with Snowflake and Tableau.

About Greenely
Greenely is on a mission to create the best customer experience for the modern energy consumer by using technology. We are a digital energy provider, helping people to lower their electricity costs by optimizing their home’s and car’s electricity usage with smart technology in an app. Greenely, backed by Nordic venture capital firms, is on a mission to enable households across the world to connect, control and optimize their energy usage. We ultimately believe that the best electricity is the one that is not being used at all, both for the wallet and the planet!

Title: Junior Analytics Associate – McKinsey Digital
Description:
Who You'll Work With
You’ll work with McKinsey Digital in Stockholm. This group brings together the best of McKinsey’s digital capabilities to help our clients use digital technology to transform their businesses.
As part of this group, you’ll join a global team working on everything from IT modernization and strategy to agile, cloud, cybersecurity, and digital transformation. You’ll typically work on projects across all industries and functions and will be fully integrated with the rest of our global firm.
You’ll also work with colleagues from across McKinsey & Company to help our clients deliver breakthrough products, experiences, and businesses, both on technology and non-technology topics.
When you join McKinsey, you are joining a firm whose culture is distinctive and inclusive. We will accelerate your development as a leader to create positive, enduring change in the world.
What You'll Do
You’ll work in teams of typically 3 - 5 consultants (incl. data scientists and data engineers), playing an active role in all aspects of client engagement, which includes gathering and analyzing information, formulating and testing hypotheses, and developing and communicating recommendations.
In this role, you’ll also have the opportunity to present results to client management and implement recommendations in collaboration with client team members.
Junior analytics associates receive exceptional training as well as frequent coaching and mentoring from colleagues on their teams. This support includes a partner from your local office or practice assigned to you to help guide your career as well as more formal training in your first few years. Additionally, you’ll receive guidance and support from your local office and practice in the selection of client projects, helping you to develop your skills and build your network.
The role of junior analytics associate with McKinsey Digital differs from our regular junior associate position in that you will be taking a hybrid role of both a management consultant and a data scientist. This will signify working on projects focused on analytics and leveraging programming to conduct more advanced analyses.
Qualifications
Degree in a technical subject, e.g. computer science, engineering, IT, hard sciences or mathematics; advanced degree is a plus
Programming experience in either Python or R
Outstanding records of academic and professional achievement
Exceptional analytical and quantitative problem-solving skills
Strong record of leadership in an academic, professional, or extracurricular setting
Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment
Ability to work effectively with people at all levels in an organization
Ability to communicate complex ideas effectively - both verbally and in writing - in English; local language is advantageous
Willingness to travel

Title: Lead Data Scientist
Description:
ArabyAds was founded in 2013 and we help our clients to acquire customers at scale using data & technology across diverse set of digital advertising inventories which are managed through four of our platforms i.e. Checkout (social commerce), iConnect (influencer marketing), Adfalcon (programmatic advertising) & DeviceBoost. We are a team of +260 passionate people across UAE, Egypt, KSA, Jordon, Lebanon & Tunisia. We are agile, fast-growing, interdisciplinary team of passionate experts in media planning, influencer marketing, consumer research, developers & coders, data scientist, artificial intelligence, and machine learning with a shared mission to create sustainable value for our clients. ArabyAds is proud to be an equal opportunity employer regardless of your race, colour, gender, religion, age, disability, or marital status. We currently have people from 16 nationalities across our 6 locations and are happy to celebrate all festivals.

Responsibilities:
Define, build, and lead a team of Data Scientists.
Design, develop and deploy Data Science projects that are production-ready, robust and optimized.
Implement data flow solutions that process data real time on message streams from source systems.
Evaluate and enhance deployed Machine Learning models.
Discover areas of the company’s processes that can be leverage machine learning
Demonstrate thorough technical knowledge of Statistical modeling, Probability and Decision theory, Operations Research techniques and other quantitative modeling techniques
Work closely with internal stakeholders like the business teams, engineering teams and partner teams and align them with respect to your focus area
Implementing and operating stable, scalable data flow solutions from production systems into end-user facing applications/reports. These solutions will be fault tolerant, self-healing and adaptive.
Work with business owners to develop and define key business questions and to build data sets that answer those questions.
Requirements:
5+ year hands-on experience with Data Science project and implementing Machine learning Models.
2+ years of experience managing Data Science teams and DS projects
An MS or PhD degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Machine Learning or related technical field
Experience in Machine learning algorithms (decision trees, multivariate and logistic regression, kNN, kMeans, etc.)
Experience in projects involving cross-functional teams
Knowledge of various machine learning techniques and key parameters that affect their performance
Depth and breadth in quantitative knowledge. Excellent quantitative modeling, statistical analysis skills and problem-solving skills
Experience processing, filtering, and presenting large quantities (Millions to Billions of rows) of data
Combination of deep technical skills and business savvy enough to interface with all levels and disciplines within our customer’s organization
Demonstrable track record of dealing well with ambiguity, prioritizing needs, and delivering results in a dynamic environment
Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to effectively advocate technical solutions to research scientists, engineering teams and business audiences
Ability to develop experimental and analytic plans for data modeling processes, use of strong baselines, ability to accurately determine cause and effect relations
Demonstrable track record of dealing well with ambiguity, prioritizing needs, and delivering results in a dynamic environment

Title: Sr Clinical Data Scientist
Description:
Description
Senior Clinical Data Scientist
Syneos Health is the only fully integrated biopharmaceutical solutions organization purpose-built to accelerate customer success. We lead with a product development mindset, seamlessly connecting our capabilities to add high-value insights to speed therapies to patients and provide practical value to help our customers achieve their objectives.
Our Clinical Development model brings the customer and the patient to the center of everything that we do. We are continuously looking for ways to simplify and streamline our work to not only make Syneos Health easier to work with, but to make us easier to work for.
Whether you join us in a Functional Service Provider partnership or a Full-Service environment, you’ll collaborate with passionate problem solvers, innovating as a team to help our customers achieve their goals. We are agile and driven to accelerate the delivery of therapies, because we are passionate to change lives.
Discover what our 29,000 employees, across 110 countries already know:
WORK HERE MATTERS EVERYWHERE
Why Syneos Health
We are passionate about developing our people, through career development and progression; supportive and engaged line management; technical and therapeutic area training; peer recognition and total rewards program.
We are committed to our Total Self culture – where you can authentically be yourself. Our Total Self culture is what unites us globally, and we are dedicated to taking care of our people.
We are continuously building the company we all want to work for and our customers want to work with. Why? Because when we bring together diversity of thoughts, backgrounds, cultures, and perspectives – we’re able to create a place where everyone feels like they belong.
Job responsibilities
Serves as Functional Lead for Clinical Data Science including primary contact for internal liaison between Clinical Data Science and Project Management, Clinical Monitoring, and other functional groups
Acts as central steward of clinical data quality, monitors risks through the holistic review of clinical and operational data, using high level knowledge of the protocol, taking into account the specific therapeutic area aspects of the protocol related to the data collected and aligning with cross functional operational plans to drive comprehensive clinical data quality
Ensures the required data elements and corresponding data quality oversight steps are identified to support the defined study analysis
Works with assigned project teams to communicate, address, troubleshoot and resolve data related questions and recommends potential solutions; escalates issues which potentially impact patient safety and study analysis
Coordinates cross functional data cleaning activities to ensure quality standards and timelines are met for clinical data deliverables Ensures the required data elements and corresponding data quality oversight steps are identified to support the defined project analysis
Drives the development of the clinical data acquisition plan and corresponding data flow diagram with the study team, assess risks associated with protocol design, study set parameters that could impact the credibility and reliability of the trial results, aligns data flow with the study protocol to ensure data collected meets regulatory and study endpoint requirements.
Drives the development of analytical tools, utilizes analytical platform/dashboard to detect potentially unreliable data that may impact the validity of the trial results Performs analytic reviews as defined in scope of work and data acquisition plan, identifies root cause to systematically resolve data issues
Monitors and communicates project progress to the Sponsor and project team including use of project status reports and tracking tools/metrics
Ensures launch, delivery and completion of all Clinical Data Sciences activities and milestones according to contractual agreement and relevant Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), guidelines, and regulations
Review, maintain budget and identify out of scope for Clinical Sciences activities, raise to PM to be implemented in required change order
Plans, manages, and requests Clinical Data Science resources for assigned projects
Coordinates the work of the assigned Clinical Data Science team
Develops and maintains project plans, specifications, and documentation in line with SOP requirements
Maintains documentation on an ongoing basis and ensures that all TMF filing is up to date for necessary files
Participates in, and presents at internal, Sponsor, third-party, and investigator meetings on behalf of clinical data science responsibilities
Prepares input, and participates in proposal bid defense meetings and request for proposals on behalf of clinical data science responsibilities
Plans for and creates necessary documentation to support internal and external audits; participates in such audits on behalf of clinical data sciences responsibilities
Trains and mentors new or junior team members
Maintains proficiency in Clinical Data Science systems and processes through regular training. May attend/represent the company at professional meetings/conferences
Performs other work-related duties as assigned. Minimal travel may be required (up to 25%)
Qualifications
What we’re looking for
BA/BS in the biological sciences, computer sciences, mathematics, or data sciences and/or related disciplines in the natural science/health care space. MS degree is preferred. In lieu of degree, equivalent relevant work experience
Clinical Data Science experience or an equivalent combination of education and experience
Experience in Clinical Data Science practices and relational database management software systems
Strong knowledge of the drug development process and its impact on data quality, in particular risk-based approach, biometrics procedures, workflows.
Aptitude for understanding analytic modeling methods such as regression, classification and clustering
Strong project management skills and knowledge of project management methodologies
Strong analytical skills and knowledge of Artificial intelligence /machine learning methodologies preferred
Demonstrated staff leadership skills
Knowledge of ALCOA++ data quality principles
Strong experience with protocol interpretation, data collection and data cleaning specification development
Experienced with data analysis/data review and visualization tool sets including but not limited to Python, R, Spotfire, SAS
Knowledge of medical terminology, clinical data, and ICH/GCP regulatory requirements for clinical studies, in particular requirements applicable to Clinical Data Sciences
Proficiency in MS Windows navigation, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and email applications
Effective oral and written communication and presentation skills
Good organizational, planning, and time management skills with the ability to multitask under tight deadlines while providing attention to detail
Ability to be flexible and adapt to change, to work independently, as well as part of a multi-disciplinary team
Ability to make effective decisions and manage multiple priorities in a highly dynamic environment
Get to know Syneos Health
Over the past 5 years, we have worked with 94% of all Novel FDA Approved Drugs, 95% of EMA Authorized Products and over 200 Studies across 73,000 Sites and 675,000+ Trial patients.
No matter what your role is, you’ll take the initiative and challenge the status quo with us in a highly competitive and ever-changing environment. Learn more about Syneos Health.
Additional Information:
Tasks, duties, and responsibilities as listed in this job description are not exhaustive. The Company, at its sole discretion and with no prior notice, may assign other tasks, duties, and job responsibilities. Equivalent experience, skills, and/or education will also be considered so qualifications of incumbents may differ from those listed in the Job Description. The Company, at its sole discretion, will determine what constitutes as equivalent to the qualifications described above. Further, nothing contained herein should be construed to create an employment contract. Occasionally, required skills/experiences for jobs are expressed in brief terms. Any language contained herein is intended to fully comply with all obligations imposed by the legislation of each country in which it operates, including the implementation of the EU Equality Directive, in relation to the recruitment and employment of its employees. The Company is committed to compliance with the Americans with Disabilities Act, including the provision of reasonable accommodations, when appropriate, to assist employees or applicants to perform the essential functions of the job.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Om teamet

Teamet AI/Analytics består av en mix av Data Engineers, Data Scientists och analytiker. Vi har tillsammans med våra kunder gjort en bredd av grejer på AI-området. För att nämna några så har vi byggt rekommendationssystem för streamingtjänster, Image-recognition-system för bilindustrin, prediktiva modeller för Arbetsförmedlingen och mycket mer. På Webstep jobbar människor från alla generationer och nationaliteter, så även i vårt AI/Analytics-team! Det gemensamma för våra anställda är intresset för kod, teknik och IT.

Att vara konsult på Webstep
Vi har en bred kundbas inom många branscher. Detta för att vi från början har lyssnat in var våra anställda vill arbeta. Det gemensamma för våra kunder är att det ofta är organisationer med stor mängd kvalitetsdata.
På Webstep vill vi verkligen göra det möjligt för var och en av våra anställda att kompetensutvecklas genom sitt uppdrag. Vårt mål är att det ska vara stimulerande och givande. Förutom detta så siktar vi på kompetensutveckling genom våra månatliga kompetensaktiviteter. Till dessa bjuder Webstep in både interna och externa föreläsare för att dela med sig av sin kunskap på olika områden. Vi tror att "Sharing is caring"!

För att passa i rollen som Data Scientist hos oss tror vi att du har..
... Jobbat som Data Scientist i minst 5 år
... Har en bakgrund i datavetenskap, systemvetenskap eller annat relevant område
... Har erfarenhet av programmering i Python och något annat språk (Java, C# etc.)
... Har arbetat med några tekniker såsom PySpark, NumPy, SciPy, Pandas, Tensorflow, Scikit-learn etc.
... Har grundläggande kunskap i svenska & engelska
... Är kommunikativ
... Vill hjälpa oss förbättra vår omvärld med hjälp av AI och Machine Learning.

Frågor om rollen som Data Scientist hos oss på Webstep?
Kontakta Petra Magnusson, Talent Acquisition Specialist, 070 288 11 67 eller petra.magnusson@webstep.se

Title: Data Scientist (Senior level) - Games
Description:
As a Data Scientist in the data science team at Embark you will be a game maker in a small team focused on supporting and leading the analytical efforts of a PVP game and delivering insights to our game team.
The Data Science team at Embark is a small team focused on making sure we have data and analysis supporting game design and development, as well as a data model and reports to serve the rest of the business.
You’ll be an integral part of a highly creative game team and together you’ll create and improve the high-quality, polished experiences we want to provide to our players. At Embark we believe in creating smaller teams of well-aligned experts that can be trusted to create games and keep them running. Some of the technologies we use to make all of those things are Python and BigQuery.

Example of responsibilities
Collaborate and work closely with game designers and business stakeholders.
Research and develop metrics and performance indicators
Extract, analyze and communicate insights from gameplay data
Apply machine learning models to better understand our players
Design telemetry logging
Communicate results clearly and concisely to all the business stakeholders
We would love if you have some of the following
Experience working with either Hadoop, BigQuery, Snowflake
Strong Programming skills in Python or R
Deep knowledge of complex SQL
Experience in predictive modeling and analysis over large datasets
Experience in building dashboards and reports using tools such as rshiny/streamlit/jupyter notebooks etc
Experience in making ETLs and data pipelines
Great written and verbal communication and presentation skills in English
Experience or interest in games


At Embark we offer competitive salaries, passionate colleagues to share knowledge with and much more, but most of all we invite you to take part of a journey into the unknown, to build creative, surprising and beautiful experiences together.
We welcome game makers of all sex, class, colour, age, gender identity, education, religion, opinion, culture, nation of origin, language, sexual orientation, shape, size, and ability.
Did we leave anyone out? Well, we welcome you, too! We think that the gaming industry is made better when everyone has a seat at the table. Be yourself at Embark and make games while doing so. Please apply with confidence. We can’t wait to hear from you (in English)!
If this role doesn't quite match what you're looking for, feel free to apply to us via our "Open Application."

Title: DATA SCIENTIST TILL GÖTEBORG
Description:
Göteborg
Vill du vara med och få TMC att växa samtidigt som du är ute på ett spännande uppdrag hos någon av våra kunder? Vi söker nu fler Data Scientists till vårt team inom Software i Göteborg. Vi är nyfikna på dig som har en kandidat- eller högskoleexamen.

| Vad förväntar vi oss av dig?
Vi lägger stor vikt vid ditt personliga engagemang och din vilja att driva din utveckling framåt. För att lyckas med det ges du chansen att själv påverka vilken typ av projekt du tar dig an samt vilken kompetensutveckling du vill investera i. Du styr din karriär helt enkelt.
Du har en kandidat- eller högskoleexamen och har minst ett års erfarenhet inom datahantering och/eller dataanalys. Vi förväntar oss att du har följande kompetenser:
God kunskap inom C++
God kunskap inom Python
Designerfarenhet av maskininlärningsmodeller
God kommunikationsförmåga i både svenska och engelska
Meriterande erfarenheter:
Tensorflow
SciPy
R (programspråk)
Agila arbetssätt
| Vad kan du förvänta dig av TMC?
Genom Employeneurship-modellen är TMC unika. Det är affärsmodellen för 2000-talets ingenjörer och den bygger på fem pelare:

A LONG TERM WORKING RELATIONSHIP
På TMC kombinerar du säkerheten av en trygg anställning med de möjligheter som entreprenörskap erbjuder. Detta eliminerar osäkerheten man kan uppleva som konsult eller entreprenör och du får mer tid och energi till att fokusera på ditt arbete och dina långsiktiga ambitioner och mål.
INDIVIDUAL PROFIT SHARING
Employeneurship-modellen erbjuder en marknadsmässig grundlön samtidigt som dina entreprenöriella förmågor premieras och du tar del av vinsten. Du som Employeneur har möjlighet att själv påverka säljprocessen utifrån din kompetens och vi är transparenta när det kommer till både din omsättning och dina kostnader. Känn ditt marknadsvärde och dela vinsten som ditt arbete genererar!
BUSINESS CELLS
Som Employeneur tillhör du en Business Cell baserat på ditt tekniska kompetensområde. Dessa specialistområden utgår från teknologiska nischkompetenser och skapar nätverk mellan dig och andra Employeneurer med liknande bakgrund. Du som Employeneur blir del av ett starkt och relevant internationellt nätverk som möjliggör ett delat engagemang i kombination med kunskaps- och erfarenhetsutbyte.
YOUNIVERSITY
TMC värderar dig som Employeneur högt och har utvecklat ett program för att garantera din personliga och professionella utveckling, din YOUrney. YOUniversity är ett unikt program för din utveckling och är tänkt att stödja dig genom din karriär. Genom personlig 1-1 coaching får du möjlighet att utvecklas, både som individ och i ditt entreprenörskap. Att ge dig möjlighet till både personlig och professionell utveckling ser vi som bästa möjliga investering!
ENTREPENEURIAL LAB
The Entrepreneurial Lab erbjuder utrymme för Employeneurer inom TMC att samarbeta över gränser. Vi vill att du ska förverkliga dina drömmar och utveckla ditt entreprenörskap. The Entrepreneurial Lab drivs av en självgående proaktiv attityd hos dig som Employeneur som skapar värde för dig själv men självklart också för våra kunder. Se The Entrepreneurial Lab som en lekplats för nya idéer, produkter som tjänster.
Eftersom TMC är ett internationellt företag kan vi erbjuda projekt på olika platser i olika länder där vi och våra kunder finns. För närvarande finns vi representerade i Sverige, Nederländerna, Belgien, Frankrike, Spanien, Portugal, Italien, U.A.E., USA och Kanada. Du får världen som arbetsplats!
| Varför Employeneurship?
Uttrycket Employeneurship kanske låter obekant, det beror på att vi uppfann det. Inte bara som ett ord utan som ett sätt att arbeta, eller till och med ett paradigm. Att vara Employeneur är mycket mer än att bara arbeta som teknisk konsult. Denna unika roll ger dig möjlighet att tänka och agera som en entreprenör i kombination med den trygghet en anställning ger. Viktigast av allt - du får en garanti för ständig utveckling och möjligheten att vara fullt ansvarig för din egen karriär.

Ta chansen att vara del av vår växande verksamhet. Ansök så pratar vi mer om din plan!

Feel Free to Contact
Christoffer Lejon
Business Manager, Sweden
Tel: +46(0)73 255 53 59

Title: Dataanalytiker/Data scientist
Description:
Vill du arbeta med dataanalys och data science?
Nu letar vi efter dig som vill arbeta på koncernens utvecklingsavdelning som dataanalytiker och/eller data scientist i vårt Business Intelligence-team. Du kommer där att bidra aktivt till koncernens vision att bli ”världens mest resurseffektiva region” genom att stärka vår datadrivna beslutsförmåga. Vi är på god väg och behöver ytterligare vässa vår affärsintelligens. Med hjälp av rapporter, statistik och nyckeltal bidrar du till att teamet levererar rätt data, till rätt person och i rätt tid. Beroende på profil använder du även AI för att skapa kreativa och värdefulla lösningar utifrån vår stora datamängd.
Dina arbetsuppgifter:
Arbeta nära verksamheten med att förstå behov och önskemål.
Ta fram BI-rapporter för beslutsstöd och analyser som stöttar våra affärsområden i deras dagliga verksamhet.
Driva arbetet med att samla in och förädla data från våra olika system.
Utforska nya affärsmöjligheter i vår stora datamängd genom nya tekniker som AI och Machine Learning.
Du som person är nyfiken, positiv och prestigelös. I teamet skapar du engagemang genom att vara engagerad och social. Du bidrar med initiativ och kreativa lösningar, samtidigt som du är ansvarstagande och kvalitetsmedveten i ditt sätt att arbeta.
Erfarenheter du tar med till oss:
Universitets- eller högskoleutbildning inom minst två av områdena statistik, dataanalys, data engineering och data science.
Arbete med dataanalys och rapportskapande i PowerBI eller liknande BI-verktyg eller plattform.
Det är meriterande om du har:
arbetat med data engineering och/eller data science.
arbetat med molnbaserade lösningar för hantering av big data.
erfarenhet från någon av domänerna finans/ekonomi, produktion, marknad, energi, elhandel.
arbetat med agil arbetsmetodik.
Vill du veta mer?
Är du intresserad av tjänsten och vill ha mer information, vänligen kontakta rekryterande chef Rasmus Lind, 076-320 21 05. Facklig information lämnas av Carina Norberg, Unionen, 013-20 92 46, Henrik Kruuse af Verchou, Akademikerföreningen, 013-20 83 56 eller Martin Eriksson, SEKO, 013-20 83 06. Ansvarig för rekryteringsprocessen är HR-partner Linn Forslund, 013-20 94 13.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
Vi arbetar med en löpande urvalsprocess så skicka in din ansökan redan idag, men senast den 12 februari 2023.
Tekniska verken bedriver samhällsviktig verksamhet, och det kan därför bli aktuellt med en säkerhetsprövning i vissa rekryteringsprocesser. När det ska genomföras så informerar vi alltid kandidaterna om detta.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Cure Media has been announced as one of the Top Influencer Marketing companies by Business of Apps in the UK, three years in a row!

As the power is shifting from companies to consumers, our mission is to help brands talk to their audience on their terms, by leveraging leading influencer channels that people trust and follow in their everyday lives. We’re growing fast and are now looking for a Data Scientist to join us on our journey to becoming the first choice for brands and influencers in Europe!
We are looking for a Data Scientist with experience and passion in advanced data analysis. Someone that is self-reliable and interested in consumer marketing behaviors. You should be interested in complex tasks and to explore new innovative solutions. As a data scientist you will continue the work to implement machine learning to predict which influencers that should be used in our campaigns. Insights that will be shared within the team and other departments in the company.
Cure Media is working with thousands of influencers in several markets such as the Nordics, Germany and the UK. This means that we also need to make trend reports on how influencer marketing differentiates between different countries.
What we offer:
The opportunity to become a partner through a stock option program.
The possibility to work with one of the fastest growing marketing channels globally, at a company in the forefront of the industry.
The role is new so you will have a big role in shaping and developing it together with our CPO.
The opportunity to play a key role in our international expansion and become part of a high-performing tech team.
We think you have:
A degree in statistics, mathematics, data science or equivalent
Experience and passion for modeling/machine learning
Good knowledge in visualizing and presenting actionable insights
Speak and write fluently in Swedish and English
Also, we think you have competencies in the following:
Python, TensorFlow, Pandas, Matplotlib, Apache, Spark, HDFS, Tidyverse, Ggplot, SQL, MongoDB
Other perks & benefits:
6 weeks paid vacation per year
Generous health package and training during working hours, e.g. Padel
MacBook and iPhone
Breakfast together every Monday
Annual conference trip
Start: ASAP (full-time)
Location & Reporting: You’ll be based in Stockholm as part of our Stockholm office and report to our founder and CPO.
Do you have any questions about the role, the career development opportunities, or something else? Get in touch with us!

Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
Senior Data Scientist
BrightBid is a rapidly growing adtech company utilising AI and human expertise to create more refined Google Ads recommendations for businesses to drive customer acquisition. Combined with BrightBid’s marketing and sales expertise, its AI- and human-led offering enables companies to compete, seeing at least a 35% increase in results on average. Founded in 2020, BrightBid is well in the top 10% of fastest growing SaaS companies globally and has achieved over 500,000 conversions for its 400+ customers.
We are a startup and we are looking for people who loves building stuff.
Who You Are
5+ years of professional experience in data science or related fields
You understand product development, and how to influence it with data analysis
You are technically proficient in SQL, python & data visualisation
You get excited from having ownership of an initiative and taking it to production.
You have a bachelors degree in Computer Science, Mathematics or any related field
You possess statistical skills to perform advanced analytics
You have experience working with large datasets
You have python coding skills and experience with analytics tools such as Pandas
Has experience taking a big idea into reality
In this role, you need to be able to communicate in English fluently
It is a merit if you know another language, but not a must.
Responsibilities
Define metrics, create key datasets, and build features
Perform exploratory big data analysis on BrightBid’s massive dataset
Collaborate closely and support product managers and engineers
Derive relevant answers and actionable insights from loosely defined problems
Why you should choose BrightBid
We have had a yearly growth of 400% since founded
We are open in 4 different markets (Stockholm Sweden, Oslo Norway, London England and Manila Philippines)
3000SEK wellness balance
All the tools you need to succeed in this role, phones, Macbooks, monitors and more if necessary!
Flexible working hours
Hybrid working place
Free breakfast at the office
An amazing team with high energy!

Title: Senior Full Stack Developer - Tech Lead
Description:
Description

How’d you like to work with an international team of passionate developers and an inspired sales team to help locals and travelers get personalised recommendations of places to see, things to do and events to attend in a city? Sounds interesting? Keep reading!

Cruncho is looking for an experienced Full Stack Developer with a backend orientation and some team leading experience, confident with the full cycle of front- and backend development. You’ll be joining a tight-knit, distributed tech team of a CTO/Backend Developer, 3 Full Stack Developers and a UI/UX Designer, working closely with the CEO and the Business Development team in shaping the development of our in-house products. In such an environment, your direct impact on Cruncho’s success and your own career is apparent.

Roles & Responsibilities

Development planning in collaboration with the tech team
Building new features from static designs (or, sometimes, just simple requirements)
Working with databases and real production data (querying, extracting reports, bulk updates, Postgres, MongoDB, Elastic Search, etc…)
Continuous development and maintenance of Cruncho’s frontend and backend apps - including a city guide, an event calendar, a quiz and a CMS.
Maintaining a consumer-focused outlook and aiding in the delivery of projects to market
Acting as a mentor to team members
Staying on top of technology trends and developments
Ensuring all technology practices adhere to regulatory standards
Shared responsibility of the product as a whole
Basic Qualifications

Masters degree in computer science or related field
A minimum of 3 years working in a technological role
A minimum of 6 month managerial experience
Advanced technological skillset and a demonstrated history with technology
Experience with responsive web UI
Experience with React, React Native, HTML & CSS (SASS)
Experience with relational and document databases
Experience with ExpressJS and TypeScript
Familiarity using Scrum/Agile development methodologies
Exceptional team management skills
Excellent verbal and written communication
Extensive industry knowledge with an eye towards the future
As a person, you are a proactive self-starter, able to work with a high level of independence while being a part of and mentoring a team. You are organised, well-structured and have an eye for details. You thrive in challenging environments, enjoy learning by doing and exhibit a drive for continuous improvement.

Additionally, you are enthusiastic about traveling and learning about new cultures. You’re optimistic, have a healthy sense of humour, and you know how to genuinely build trust and long-term relationships.

Finally, you are highly proficient in both spoken and written English.

Optional/Preferred Qualifications

Familiarity with the start-up environment
Experience with web scraping
Google Analytics, Matomo (or other analytics platforms)
HTML emails
Redux
Basic UI/UX design
Image editing software (e.g. Photoshop, Figma, Sketch, etc)
Some knowledge and/or experience of AI / Machine Learning.
Additionally, proficiency in additional language(s) is appreciated.

Perks

Being part of a growing business in an exciting market
Beautiful office in city-centre offering a flexible co-working space, free breakfasts, yoga sessions, afterworks...
Flexible working hours

Ideal start: Nov/Dec 2022

Employment: fulltime

Salary: level to be discussed depending on seniority. Stock option program.

Location: Odenplan, Stockholm’s city-centre, Sweden. Company private office part of a co-working space providing us with a flexible work environment.
