Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
Founded in 2018, Kreditz is already the market leader in PSD2-credit scoring products.
We use Open Banking/PSD2-technology to create our revolutionizing real-time credit scoring products, which are beloved by banks, financial institutions, iGaming companies and many more. Kreditz products enable consumers, and businesses, to gain financial inclusion, and financial opportunity where none would be available with traditional credit scoring systems.
Our long-term vision "One world, One score" translates into our everyday mission of financial inclusion, and financial opportunity, for everyone around the globe
– Everyone deserves a fair assessment.
Come join us on our impactful mission!

ABOUT THE POSITION
Thanks to 18 months of unbroken growth (+310% FY21 vs FY20) we are now looking to increase our analytics organization further with an awesome Data Science ‘magician’ eager to advance Kreditz revolutionizing products even further alongside a team of credit scoring experts, mathematicians and genuinely passionate colleagues.
We are currently entering an exciting phase (startup>scaleup) where we will expand our market presence further, from the Nordics to selected countries in Europe. Our clients range from some of Europe’s largest banks and iGaming companies to smaller, innovative businesses.
As a Senior Data Scientist at Kreditz, your playing field is data, vast amount of data. Our products and services are highly data driven, and to remain innovative you need to be confident in the analysis of both the known, and the unknown. Kreditz expects you to be able to analyze large internal and external data sets, make data driven conclusions, and evaluate your findings to optimize Kreditz algorithms and statistical models. This role is an important part of Kreditz growing analytics team, which is led by our CAO.
If you share the excitement to work with state-of-the-art technology within Open Banking/PSD2, and to deliver market leading solutions that make a positive impact on our society, all the while being part of a growth journey across the world – this is the right position for you!

WHAT CAN KREDITZ OFFER
One-way ticket to an amazing growth journey you will never forget – A journey where everyone in the team plays a central role for our company’s success
Fun-loving, passionate, and talented colleagues with whom to share small and big, company and personal, milestones and accomplishments
Humble corporate culture – we celebrate all wins, no matter the size, together
24/7 access to gym/sauna/sports center at our office PLUS additional wellness allowance

TASKS
Some of the tasks you will be performing, and lead, as a Senior Data Scientist at Kreditz:
Management and structuring of vast amounts of data
Analysis, interpretations and predictions of data
Transaction categorization and exploration (NLP, classification)
Optimization of Kreditz algorithms and statistical models
Support junior colleagues in their analytical work
Lead model development, follow-ups and performance evaluation
Model ownership, including development and implementation
Project lead in both client- and internal projects
Proactive data driven product development together with Product owner

WE ARE LOOKING FOR
A colleague who is analytical, structured and communicative. Someone who (like us) is up for the BIG challenge to disrupt traditional credit scoring systems via Open Banking/PSD2-technology. To be successful in this role, you must have a positive
“We can do it” mindset, along with an appreciation of working in a fast-paced growth company. You are comfortable in being independent in your daily work as well as acting with responsibility both towards your colleagues and clients.
Additionally, we believe that you have:
+5 yrs experience from financial services/tech/insurance/consulting or equivalent relevant experience
A relevant academic background (Engineering, Data/IT, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics)
Proven experience from DL/ML/NPL projects within relevant industry
The ability to take your analysis and models to production deployment
Confident in coding languages such as: Python, R and SQL
Very good communications skills in English (speech/writing), Swedish or other language skills is meritorious
Credit risk modeling from bank or financial institutions is meritorious
Experience from PSD2/Open Banking is meritorious

APPOINTMENT OF ROLE
Q4 2022
SCOPE
Full time, permanent employment (tillsvidareanställning)
SALARY
Fixed monthly salary
REPORTING
You will be reporting to the company's CAO
WORKPLACE
Our office is in Danderyd, Stockholm.
RECRUITMENT PROCESS
We interview candidates on an ongoing basis (ongoing selection)

CONTACT
Lorenzo Puccio, COO, lorenzo@kreditz.com
If you want to know more about the role, feel free to reach out to Magnus Källhager, Chief Analytics Officer, magnus@kreditz.com , +4670-7913984

Title: Nyexaminerad Data Scientist till världsledande företag!
Description:
Har du en passion för att leverera affärsnytta med nya tekniker och vill utveckla dig själv, samtidigt som du utvecklar våran kunds verksamhet? Just nu söker ett välkänt bolag i Göteborg en Nyexaminerad Data Scientist med ett finansiellt intresse - varmt välkommen in med din ansökan omgående då vi tillämpar löpande urval!

Om tjänsten:
Vi på Friday söker nu för kunds räkning en Nyexaminerad Data Scientist med ett finansiellt intresse till ett bolag som är världsledande inom flera branscher. Teamet som denna roll ska ingå i bygger verktyg med syfte att använda dessa i beslutsunderlag - där målet är att optimera olika kapaciteter vad gäller intäkter och kostnader med visionen att göra dessa processer enklare och mer lönsamma genom att erbjuda nya kognitiva verktyg. Här arbetar du nära tillsammans med ett mindre team av datavetare för att behandla och analysera data i syfte att stödja affärsbeslut.

Exempel på arbetsuppgifter:
Behandla och analysera data.
Optimera olika kapaciteter vad gäller intäkter och kostnader.
Utöva kontakt med-, och direkt arbete för kunder.

Vi söker dig som:
Har en eftergymnasial utbildning, gärna som civilingenjör inom IT, eller motsvarande.
Goda kunskaper i Python.
Intresse för ekonomi.
Behärskar engelska och svenska flytande, då båda språken kommuniceras internt och externt.

Vidare kommer stor vikt läggas vid personlig lämplighet. Du föredrar att arbeta i team och ser det som ett tillfälle att lära från dina kollegor, likväl som att själv få stötta och delge egen erfarenhet och kunskap vid behov. Vi ser vi gärna att du är en positiv medarbetare som håller ett lösningsfokus genomgående i processer och projekt.

Om anställningen:
Detta är ett konsultuppdrag vilket innebär att du till en början kommer vara anställd av Friday. Ambitionen från kundföretaget och vår sida är att du därefter blir direktanställd hos dem.

Övrig info:
Omfattning: Heltid.
Start: Juni 2023.
Placering: Göteborg/ Möjlighet till att arbeta remote.
Rekryteringsansvarig: Gabriella Bergström.
Lön: Månadslön.

Ansök genom att klicka på länken nedan. Kom ihåg att vara snabb med din ansökan då vi gör löpande urval av kandidater och att annonsen kan stängs ner innan tjänsten är tillsatt om vi gått över till urvals- och intervjufasen.

Om Friday:
Genom att vara en partner både till våra kandidater och kunder strävar vi efter att hitta den bästa matchningen. Det gör vi genom att lära känna våra kunder och kandidater på riktigt! Vi ser självklart till att kunskaps- och erfarenhetskrav matchar, men framförallt lägger vi vikt vid samsyn kring värderingar och företagskultur som båda parter värdesätter.

Vår passion är att hjälpa människor till rätt roll, arbetsplats och sammanhang inom IT och teknik. Därför grundade vi Friday med ambition att hjälpa dig till jobbet som ger dig fredagskänslan – varje dag!

Vi riktar oss främst till dig som är i början av din karriär eller studerar vid högskola/universitet inom IT och Teknik. Vår övertygelse är att människor uppnår sin fulla potential när man ser fram emot att gå till jobbet varje morgon. ”Friday – everyday”, hur låter det?

Title: Product Manager - Data Foundations
Description:
Tink was founded in 2012, and a decade later became part of Visa in 2022. Tink was created with the aim of changing the banking industry for the better. We have built Europe’s most robust open banking platform – with the broadest, deepest connectivity and powerful services that create value out of the financial data. We offer the tools that allow anyone – from big banks and fintechs to startups – to build the future of financial services across Europe.
The Data Foundation area fuels our decisions and innovation across all of our products and services by providing a reliable and scalable data platform and tooling. We work across Tink serving a wide range of areas and needs from business insights and product analytics to external reporting, machine learning and data applications. Now is the time to take it to the next level.

In this role, you will be responsible for defining and championing our data strategy and roadmap by managing data platform teams. You will own the tools, infrastructure and processes that allow everyone at Tink to quickly turn data into actionable insights and powerful data products.

We think that you either come from a solid product management background and are excited to venture into the data domain, or that you have been working as a data analyst, data scientist or data engineer and after some exposure to Product Management you are now interested in taking on a new type of role. If you have experience of both, that’s even better.

In this role you will:
Be part of two teams that design, build and operate data flows within Tink’s data platform
Work tirelessly to gain a deep understanding of the needs of your stakeholders - from data scientists and developers in other product teams, to product analysts, customer success managers and finance teams
Define goals and milestones for your teams and work side by side with your team members, the engineering manager and other product teams and stakeholders to ensure the goals are reached
Evaluate and measure the impact of your teams’ work and ensure that it contributes to reaching Tink’s overall goals
Run some of the team's day-to-day activities and ceremonies: retros, standups, groomings and plannings
Communicate overall status to stakeholders


What we’re looking for:
Experience of working either as a product manager or in a data analyst/scientist/engineer role possibly exposed to Product Management
Eagerness to take Tink data and Products to the next level
Constant drive for ensuring your work has a measurable impact on Tink’s business, by continuously looking for ways to validate the value you are creating
High sense of urgency and commitment; we always strive to make things happen
Proven ability to work cross-functionally in a highly collaborative environment
Mindset of looking for pragmatic solutions and balancing quality and time to delivery depending on the situation
Previous experience working with cloud based data platforms such as GCP, AWS or similar
Desire to work in a fast-paced, results-driven environment with multiple responsibilities
Who we are at Tink
We are a company of developers and engineers – it’s in our DNA to imagine, build and iterate. We were founded with a vision of transforming an industry that lacked competition and momentum. And we have built a company of passionate over-achievers who all believe there is always a better way of doing things.
People from all over Europe – and the world – have joined us on our mission to build the biggest and best open banking platform in Europe.
We're looking forward to your application!

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.
For further information see www.babyshop.com
ABOUT THE POSITION
Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.
WHAT YOU'LL DO
Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE
You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...
Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.
Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!
Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Analytics Engineer
Description:
At Epidemic Sound we are reinventing the music industry. Our carefully curated catalog, with over 35,000 tracks, is tailored for storytellers, streaming services, and in-store soundtracks. Countless clients around the world, from broadcasters, production companies, DSPs, and YouTubers rely on our tracks to help them tell their stories. Epidemic Sound’s music is heard in hundreds of millions of online videos daily, across millions of playlist streams, and in thousands of in-store locations. Headquartered in Stockholm, we’re spread across offices in New York City, Los Angeles, Seoul, Hamburg, and Amsterdam. We’re growing fast, have lots of fun, and are taking the music industry with us.
We’re now looking for an Analytics Engineer to join our central Data engineering team, the team that is responsible for our Data Platform. You will play a vital role in ingesting data from our data lake into the data warehouse, where data will be transformed, scheduled, and made ready to be used for analytics & product development teams. You might come from a background where you have passion for Data Modeling or Data Engineering. Or you might have worked as a Data Scientist or Data Analyst and you’re curious and want to work more with Data Engineering.
In order for you to thrive in this role, we believe that you have one or more of the following:
Experience in SQL and Python
A strong interest and curiosity in data – you might have also worked with large-scale data warehouses like BigQuery or Snowflake, data modelling, and/or relational model design
Experience in any of the following tooling: Terraform, Snowplow, Apache Airflow, Fivetran, Looker, OpsGenie
Experience with cloud computing such as GCP or AWS
You definitely have the following:
A love for teamwork
A love for continuous improvement and learning
Follow best software engineering practices in your work
The ability to communicate in English with professional working proficiency
You value best practices but realize that all rules have exceptions
A passion for sharing your knowledge and teaching others what you know
Nice to have experience:
dbt
Previous experience working with or setting up ELT-like data pipelines

How you will make an impact
You would join Epidemic’s Data Engineering team, with a mission to provide the platform, tools, solutions, and data sets that enable the company to stay ever more data-informed. As an Analytics Engineer, you would play a key role in bridging Data Engineering and Data Analytics.
Our modern data stack runs on Google Cloud Platform and part of our solution stack includes BigQuery as a data warehouse, Google Cloud Composer (Airflow) for data pipeline orchestration, Dataflow jobs for data processing, and dbt for data transformation.

You can expect to:
Join an organization with passionate Data Scientists and Data Engineers at an early stage of the company's history. This is a chance to be part of building a data analytics platform that scales worldwide
Design, build and maintain the Epidemic data models
Drive data architecture matters, including following the data definition and data modeling principles across all parts of the business, and ensuring that everything from tracking to reporting cubes adheres to Epidemic’s best practices
Act as a stakeholder and partner with both engineering teams and analytics teams to deliver well-defined, tested, and high-quality data sets
Work with business stakeholders and design data models to quantitatively support everything from corporate strategy to user acquisition
Support and mentor analytics consumers on best software engineering practices
This role will include finding ways to share learnings across the organization. It could be via internal talks, writing internal blog posts, or any other way you may think of. You can also expect to learn a ton of new things, be it through hack-days, courses, conferences, or tech talks. We emphasize learning and we also expect you to share your knowledge with your colleagues.
We collaborate constantly and are big believers in teamwork and the value of practices like careful code reviews and pair (or mob) programming. On top of this, you can expect to have lots of fun and take pride in what you and all of Epidemic is doing.

Curious to learn more about who we are and what we do? Check out our brand new "About us" page https://www.epidemicsound.com/about-us/

We have lots of fun soundtracking the world and our annual Spring Bash is an event that captures this perfectly. Take a look at our most recent one, a virtual celebration!

Application
Do you want to be a part of our fantastic team? Please apply, in English, by clicking the link below.
We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business, and a better world. We value diversity and encourage everyone to come and soundtrack the world with us.

Title: Deep Learning Researcher
Description:
AI is changing the world as we know it. Despite all advancements in the field, there are still many grand challenges waiting for a solution. One of these challenges, and the mission of Embedl, is to make Deep Learning more efficient so that it can be deployed everywhere with low cost and low energy consumption. We want to enable the next wave of advanced AI powered applications and we want you to join us in this mission!
The Role
You will join our research team to help us develop the world's best methods for making Deep Learning efficient. You will both develop your own novel methods as well as evaluate approaches from academia. More specifically you will work with Deep Learning compression, automated hyper-parameter tuning and network architecture search to make Deep Learning efficient.
Who are you?
We are looking for an outstanding individual with excellent problem solving skills and demonstrated achievements of academic or industrial research in Deep Learning. You are ambitious, self-driven and thrive when given high-level responsibilities and problems to solve. You should be a team player, willing to both learn from others and teach others, and generally contribute to a positive working environment.
You must have
PhD or M.Sc. in Computer Science, Physics, Electrical Engineering, or make a great case for your equivalent skills achieved via experience (excellent grades required)
3+ years of experience in industry or academia pushing the current state-of-the-art of Deep Learning
Proficient coding skills in Python and C/C++, working in a UNIX environment and using git
We would be super-happy if you also have

Experience with Deep Learning compression, automated hyper-parameter optimization and/or Network Architecture Search
Who are we?
Embedl is a spin-out from the European Commission Horizon 2020 funded research project LEGaTO. The mission of EmbeDL is to develop and commercialize its Deep Learning optimization engine into a highly scalable platform that makes DL-based AI affordable and energy efficient in embedded systems. The DL optimization engine bridges the gap between data scientist (experts in AI algorithms) and computer engineers (experts in hardware).
Embedl has close connections to academic research, Swedish industry and innovation ecosystem as well as well-established connections to venture capital.
Application process
Please send in your application in English as soon as possible. For any questions and clarifications connect or reach out to ann@embedl.com.
You are welcome at Embedl for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what your favorite IDE is.

Title: Data Science Lead
Description:
Följ med på vår resa mot ett hållbart samhälle! SJ – Framtidens sätt att resa.
SJ är på en resa. En resa där målet är att bidra till ett hållbart samhälle genom att möjliggöra klimatsmart resande, i Sverige och i Norden. Vägen dit kantas av en mängd spännande möjligheter och utmaningar de kommande åren.
Vi växer och utvecklas inom hela verksamheten. Mångmiljardinvesteringar i nya moderna tåg, investeringar i digitala system för att effektivisera vår verksamhet, kompetensutveckling av vår personal, listan kan göras lång. Allt detta görs med kunden i fokus och med målet att göra det möjligt för fler att göra det hållbara resevalet.
Till huvudkontoret på Vasagatan 10 i Stockholm, söker vi nu en Data Science Lead som en grundläggande del i att etablera SJs Data & Analys-avdelning och genom det bidra till vår långsiktiga framgång.
I den här rollen är du ansvarig för att samla och utveckla SJ-koncernens Data Scientists genom att både själv driva djupgående initiativ liksom att organisera och stötta data science-arbetet tvärs koncernen. Organisatoriskt tillhör du SJ-koncernens centrala avdelning för Data & Analys och rapporterar till chefen för Data & Analys. Arbetet sker dels i nära samarbete med närmsta gruppen, dels med övriga på SJ som arbetar med avancerad/operationaliserad analys. Rollen är en av de första pusselbitarna som läggs för att skapa grunden till ett mer datadrivet SJ och avdelningen Data & Analys har som uppdrag att driva och guida koncernen framåt på den resan. Vi söker därför en driven och erfaren Data Scientist som kan leda i arbetet att låsa upp den outnyttjade potential som finns i våra omfattande datatillgångar.
Vem söker vi?
Vi söker dig med gedigen erfarenhet av avancerad/operationaliserad analys i komplexa och storskaliga miljöer tillsammans med god förmåga och intresse för att leda andra i en virtuell organisation. I botten har du akademisk examen inom matematiktung inriktning, exempelvis ingenjörsutbildning med fokus på matematik, statistik, datavetenskap, data science eller motsvarande. Du har erfarenhet av olika tekniska plattformar och programmeringsspråk och är väl insatt i hur samverkan med systemutvecklare, data engineers och kravställare kan och bör ske i en agil omgivning. Antagligen har du erfarenhet från en mogen kontext sett till förmåga att utvinna värde från data men har ett intresse för att själv vara med och bygga upp något liknande från grunden.
Du är självgående, nyfiken och ansvarstagande samt får energi av att växla mellan mer övergripande strukturella uppgifter och de som kräver en mer handfast och detaljerad insats.
Arbetsbeskrivning
Som Data Science Lead ansvarar du för att etablera, driva och utveckla samarbete i tvärfunktionellt community med de inom SJ som arbetar med data science-relaterade frågor. I detta ingår till en början att samla gruppen och fokusera dess medlemmar till gemensamma arbetssätt och verktyg för att sen tillsammans utforska nya möjligheter. Arbetet innebär även att bidra till den strategiska planen för hur SJs förmåga kopplat till data science ska utvecklas.
Arbetet bygger alltså på kontinuerlig dialog med koncernens alla delar och att identifiera och samla in utvecklingsbehov för att sedan prioritera dessa för genomförande. Du kommer att stödja andra och även driva egna utvecklingsinitiativ, vissa från grunden och andra genom att vidareutveckla och underhålla sedan tidigare framtagna lösningar.
Ambitionen är att på sikt utöka avdelningen Data & Analys med ytterligare Data Scientist-förmåga vilket då kommer innebära att uppgiften som Data Science Lead växer i form av ett arbetsledningsansvar.
Vad kan SJ erbjuda dig?
På SJ ger vi dig goda möjligheter och utrymme att påverka och bidra till utveckling. Det här är en utmanande och intressant roll som erbjuder frihet i kombination med stort ansvar. En roll som bidrar till, och möjliggör, ett hållbart resande. SJs utveckling och tillväxt har varit och förväntas långsiktigt att vara mycket god. Vår flexibilitet och förmåga att anpassa verksamheten till verkligheten har utvecklats till en av bolagets styrkor.
Kontakt
I den här rekryteringen samarbetar SJ med Jefferson Wells. För mer information om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Malin Magnusson 076-780 68 64.
Vi ser gärna att du skickar in din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast 15 feb.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
SJ vet att mångfald ger fler perspektiv och ökar SJs konkurrenskraft. Vi välkomnar därför sökanden med olika bakgrunder som vill vara med och bidra till ett inkluderande arbetsklimat.
SJ för människor närmare varandra, varje dag.
SJ är ett svenskt reseföretag som erbjuder hållbara tågresor i egen regi och i samarbete med andra. SJ är ett av Sveriges grönaste varumärken och en del av lösningen för att klimatmålen ska nås. Koncernens 5400 medarbetare i Sverige och Norge bidrar alla till ökat tågresande – framtidens sätt att resa.
Som marknadsledande tågoperatör knyter SJ ihop Sverige, Norge, liksom Skandinaviens huvudstäder och varje dag möts våra kunder och medarbetare på någon av våra 1500 avgångar från över 400 stationer. SJ ägs av svenska staten och har som uppdrag att driva lönsam persontrafik på järnväg.

Title: Data Scientist (Senior level) - Games
Description:
As a Data Scientist in the data science team at Embark you will be a game maker in a small team focused on supporting and leading the analytical efforts of a PVP game and delivering insights to our game team.

The Data Science team at Embark is a small team focused on making sure we have data and analysis supporting game design and development, as well as a data model and reports to serve the rest of the business.

You’ll be an integral part of a highly creative game team and together you’ll create and improve the high-quality, polished experiences we want to provide to our players. At Embark we believe in creating smaller teams of well-aligned experts that can be trusted to create games and keep them running. Some of the technologies we use to make all of those things are Python and BigQuery.

Example of responsibilities

Collaborate and work closely with game designers and business stakeholders.
Research and develop metrics and performance indicators
Extract, analyze and communicate insights from gameplay data
Apply machine learning models to better understand our players
Design telemetry logging
Communicate results clearly and concisely to all the business stakeholders
We would love if you have some of the following

Experience working with either Hadoop, BigQuery, Snowflake
Strong Programming skills in Python or R
Deep knowledge of complex SQL
Experience in predictive modeling and analysis over large datasets
Experience in building dashboards and reports using tools such as rshiny/streamlit/jupyter notebooks etc
Experience in making ETLs and data pipelines
Great written and verbal communication and presentation skills in English
Experience or interest in games
At Embark we offer competitive salaries, passionate colleagues to share knowledge with and much more, but most of all we invite you to take part of a journey into the unknown, to build creative, surprising and beautiful experiences together.

We welcome game makers of all sex, class, colour, age, gender identity, education, religion, opinion, culture, nation of origin, language, sexual orientation, shape, size, and ability.

Did we leave anyone out? Well, we welcome you, too! We think that the gaming industry is made better when everyone has a seat at the table. Be yourself at Embark and make games while doing so. Please apply with confidence. We can’t wait to hear from you (in English)!

If this role doesn't quite match what you're looking for, feel free to apply to us via our " Open Application. (https://www.embark-studios.com/jobs/278181-game-maker-open-application)"

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Life at Winningtemp

Winningtemp offers the market an unique and revolutionary technology for creating successful work places. This is done by collecting and visualizing real-time data that describes the employee's experience of leadership, meaningfulness, control and joy at work.
Today, Winningtemp consists of a wonderful and ambitious group of 115+ people in the offices in Gothenburg, Stockholm, Oslo and London. The head quarter is newly renovated (of course with a lot of purple) in the middle of central Gothenburg.

At Winningtemp we care about the well-being of our employees and therefore we of course work continuously with our own tool to be an attractive employer. We have grown by over 2100% in recent years and we continue to grow.
By 2024, our goal is to make an impact on more than 4 million people through our product.

So what is the role about?

As a Data Engineer at Winningtemp, you will work with many different internal stake holders, with a focus on maintaining data, creating data tools and improving internal processes within your area.
Your mission is to ensure that our data generates actionable and valuable results for the business, and ultimately our customers. You will have an important role linked to an important mission of ours; to become One Winningtemp throughout the whole organization.

Other areas of responsibilities;
Create and maintain optimal data pipeline architecture
Assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional/ non-functional business requirements
Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements; automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability
Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation, and loading of data from a wide variety of data sources using SQL and DataBricks ‘big data’ technologies
Build analytics tools that utilize the data pipeline to provide actionable insights into customer acquisition, operational efficiency, and other key business performance metrics
Work with internal stakeholders to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs
Keep our data secured and compliant across national boundaries
Create data tools for business and product team members that assist them in building and optimizing our business operations and product into an innovative industry leader
Work with data and analytics experts to strive for greater functionality in our data system
Your team and manager ‍‍‍

In this role you will work close to our senior Data scientist, Miroslav, someone you will have daily communication with. Miroslav has two PhDs, including one in artificial intelligence from Stockholm University. He has eight years of experience in academia - during which his research was funded by some of the most prestigious fellowships available, including the Marie-Sklodowska Currie Fellowship. Miroslav works in Stockholm, but this position is also available in Gothenburg.
Miroslav is a very appreciated colleague, dedicated and eager to share his knowledge and experience in the field, everything to make you learn as much as possible.
In this role, you will also be working close to all our different departments, meaning you will have collaboration over the whole organization.

You will be reporting to our CFO and be a part of his team. The CFO is situated in Gothenburg.

Are you the one we are looking for?

Winningtemp is the place where we all succeed together, something that you also feel is essential in your daily work, teamwork makes the dreamwork. You are therefor a team player and enjoy sharing ideas and learnings with the people around you.

You appreciate to plan your work well, and always complete what you've started. You set high goals for yourself, and always does what it takes to achieve good results. In addition to that, you look outside the box to think in new ways, meaning you are good at finding solutions to problems that arise. You are up-to-date in your area of expertise, and you have a great interest in always learning more about new techniques and systems within your area.

You have 4+ years of experience in a Data Engineer role, and you have a degree, or its equivalent, in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information System or similar. You have advanced SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases. You have been building and optimizing ‘big data’ data pipelines, architectures, and data sets. You have been working with structured and unstructured datasets, and you are used to build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency, and workload management. You have successfully manipulated, processed, and extracted value from large disconnected datasets.
You have experience in using one and/or several following software and tools:
Big data tools: Spark (preferred), Hadoop, Kafka, etc.
Relational SQL databases
Data pipeline and workflow management tools
Azure Databricks, Data Factory or similar
Object-oriented/object function scripting languages: Python, R or similar
Experience with business intelligence tools, for example Power BI
Nice to haves:
HR tech platform/tool industry experience
Previous experience from working in a start up/scale up
No worries if you do not experience in all of the areas and/or tools, we will guide you along the way!

What's in it for me?
A fun and evolving opportunity to learn a lot and to actual have an impact, both professionally and on a personal level
Committed and dedicated colleagues, and closest manager, who not only laugh together at work, but also outside of work at events, AWs, kickoff etc.
Be a part of the journey and innovation of a scale up providing a meaningful product for our customers
30 days vacation and advance holiday
Generous wellness allowance
Great pension and insurance offer


Why Winningtemp?

As an employee at Winningtemp, you will be part of our purple family
With us, you will find energetic and loyal colleagues who help each other succeed together. With us, everyone is equally valuable, regardless of gender, ethnicity and background. Diversity is also something we work actively with and something we value. We share happiness every day, not only for our product and the work we do, but also for each other. The commitment of each employee is what really makes us stand out from other companies. You can expect a supportive workplace where everyone works together towards our vision; to forever change how people succeed together!
We promise you; you will be impressed!

Our recruitment process includes;

Personality and logical test -> Interview with recruiter -> Interview with the future manager -> Interview with closest colleague -> Reference check -> Offer

We handle applications continuously so don't hesitate to apply as soon as possible!

Title: Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
We’re Findify by Maropost, an agile team focused on delivering the industry’s best search and merchandising tool for ecommerce. A fully remote team with great experience & grand ambitions, spread around all over Europe.

Headquartered in Downtown Toronto with offices also in Australia, India, and Europe, Maropost is the leader in unified commerce for the midmarket! Our Software as a Service platform provides organizations with the ability to connect with their customers across Ecommerce, Retail, Marketing, Service and Search Clouds to unify the customer experience as well as to provide efficiency, value, and ROI to their organizations.

About the Position:
As a Machine Learning Engineer, you'll be one of the owners of our personalisation and recommendations engine. It consists of many moving parts, starting with data collection, processing it via Flink and all the way to ML model development, training, serving and A/B testing.
As an expert in your field, you will be empowered to steer the future direction of our ML capabilities and will be, together with the help of the core backend team, responsible for serving the innovations to our customers in an efficient and reliable way.
We’re an empowered product team, firmly committed to collaborative problem solving. We write specs and share the decision making. We work in two-week sprints to deliver greatness.

The Opportunity:
We are looking for an open minded and enthusiastic data scientist for our Senior Machine Learning Engineer position to join our Machine Learning team. If you are interested in personalization and information retrieval and have experience in this field, we would love to meet you! We are a product driven team, so we’re looking for someone who loves to be engaged in the product development process and appreciates being able to deliver a feature without depending on other engineers.

About the Position:
As a data scientist on our Machine Learning team, you'll be one of the owners of our personalisation and recommendations engine. It consists of many moving parts, starting with data collection, processing it via Flink and all the way to ML model development, training, serving and A/B testing.
As an expert in your field, you will be empowered to steer the future direction of our ML capabilities and will be, together with the help of the core backend team, responsible for serving the innovations to our customers in an efficient and reliable way.
We’re an empowered product team, firmly committed to collaborative problem solving. We write specs and share the decision making. We work in two-week sprints to deliver greatness.

What You'll be Responsible for:
Designing and implementing maintainable ML services, and driving projects from start to finish.
Exploring explainable ML and control over it, we believe ML model's performance is already good and this has a huge growth potential.
Keeping up-to-date with advancements in the field of AI/ML to make sure our algorithms reflect the current state of the art.
Reading a lot of code, writing code with a focus on maintainability.
Contributing to technical and product specs, and collaborating on architecture and design decisions together with the other stakeholders.
Embracing feedback on your specs and your code as an opportunity for continuous improvement and collaborative design, and carrying out spec and code review for your coworkers.
Caring for knowledge transfer and mentoring others on the team, whether they're overall more junior or just less experienced in your specific domain of expertise.
Being an effective technical and non-technical communicator (our company language is English).

What You'll need to bring to Maropost
Have previous experience developing and iterating on machine learning models (We use Python to train our Learn-to-Rank model).
Have previous experience with serving and maintaining the ML model (We use Scala for to serve our models).
Understand statistics and experimental design.
Are comfortable reading and writing SQL queries.
Have previous experience working with data processing pipelines (we use Flink, but experience with Spark or similar tools will be sufficient).
Appreciate good developer experience and make ours even better by introducing new tools and iterating on processes.
Are generous with your communication, whether it is about new ideas, praise, or very kindly phrased constructive feedback.
Like to learn new things, have an open mind and want to share your knowledge with your coworkers.

What’s in it for you?
You will not only have the freedom to make this role your own but be part of helping grow the Retail Global brand and expand it into all our markets globally as we currently operate in North America, Europe and ANZ (Australia/New Zealand). If you want to work with other brilliant people in an extraordinary work culture and are eager to learn (and have fun) along the way, then Maropost is the place for you!


You'll also have access to these perks:
Extended Healthcare
Stock Options
Dental Care
Vision Care
Impact and culture
We are going into a growth phase so this is the perfect opportunity for you if you're excited about joining a team where you can have a lot of impact and take a lot of ownership over your work. The TypeScript team especially is a great opportunity for you if you want to leave your mark and contribute to the culture, as the team's position is becoming strategically more prominent with more of the core functionality of the software getting moved to the domain of the TypeScript team.

Developer experience
We are a high-tech company, and especially in the recent years we've focused a lot on developer experience. We have a cutting-edge tech stack (TypeScript and Scala with Kubernetes deployments) with no legacy tools and a keen interest in keeping it that way - so if you're excited about learning new technologies in a laid back, collaborative environment where quality software and engineering experience are among the first priorities, we are a good fit for you.

Work life balance
We're a remote team and have found this a recipe for success for the whole company. This has made us successful especially during the global pandemic where we've been able to grow the company and keep all positions intact while supporting our staff with young children and other family members to care for. We care about quality of work, collaborative processes and tangible results - we want you to be available and responsive during usual working hours in case your coworkers need something from you, but we’re very flexible when the circumstances arise. We have kids at home from daycare making appearances on calls sometimes, and you can book a slot in your work calendar for the appointment with your doctor or your dentist without feeling guilty. It’s important that we’re communicative and as responsive as possible when that happens, but sometimes we need some flexibility on when we get the focused work done and we understand that completely.

Equal Employment Opportunist:
Maropost is deeply committed to promoting diversity, advancing equity and fostering a culture of inclusion. Therefore, we invite applications from marginalized and equity-seeking groups. Individuals seeking employment at Maropost are considered without regards to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identification, national origin, age, marital status, ancestry, physical or mental disability, or veteran status. Accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process. Please feel free to alert us of any accommodations via hr@maropost.com.

Vi på Sogeti gillar människor. Och teknik. Med teknikens hjälp gör vi vardagen bättre för människor och företag och bygger lösningar som effektiviserar och håller, länge.
Gillar du också människor och teknik och vad vi kan åstadkomma tillsammans? Trivs du med att arbeta i en ledande roll, nära kunder och medarbetare? Är du lösningsorienterad, kommunikativ och bra på att se helheten? Då kanske du är en av oss.

Har en bred förståelse för IT och systemutvecklig
Är utåtriktad, kommunikativ och positiv

Brinner för kundnöjdhet och har erfarenhet av att driva kunddialogen i projekten
Meriterande
Erfarenhet av att arbeta agilt och/eller enligt traditionella metodiker
