Title: Data & Analytics Consultants
Description:
Data has the power to fundamentally change companies and their business models. Businesses that manage to turn data into actionable insight will have a great competitive advantage. BearingPoint’s Data & Analytics team combine broad business understanding with deep technology expertise in order to help our clients make insight driven decisions on all levels of their organization. We help our clients explore the full potential of their data using modern tools and technologies and are currently looking to strengthen our team.
What we are looking for:
Top performing individuals with the following characteristics and background:
Passion for technology and transforming data to business value
Desire to work both with technical development and advisory services
A business mindset and strong analytical skills
Hands on experience with Data & Analytics methods such as Data Management, Business Intelligence, and Machine learning
Experience with SQL, R, Python, PowerBI, Tableau or similar tools
Excellent communication skills both written and spoken
Master’s degree with excellent academic record
1+ years in consulting within the area of Data & Analytics
Fluency in Swedish and English (both written and spoken)
For the right candidate, we can offer:
A unique opportunity to carry out challenging Data & Analytics projects including both strategic advisory and implementation of data solutions and -analyses
Exciting career opportunities and possibilities to learn and grow as fast as you can handle
Highly competent and down to earth colleagues
An informal and “Easy to work with” culture
Competitive compensation and benefits
Please apply by submitting your CV and personal letter as soon as possible, selection is ongoing.
About BearingPoint
BearingPoint is an independent management and technology consultancy firm with European roots and a global reach. The company operates in three units: Consulting, Solutions and Ventures. Consulting covers the advisory business; Solutions provides the tools for successful digital transformation, regulatory technology and advanced analytics; Ventures drives the financing and development of start-ups. BearingPoint’s clients include many of the world’s leading companies and organizations. The firm has a global consulting network with more than 10,000 people and supports clients in over 75 countries, engaging with them to achieve measurable and sustainable success.

For more information, please visit: www.bearingpoint.com

Title: Product Owner - Data & Analytics
Description:
Vill du jobba i ett företag med både hjärta och hjärna som satsar mycket på IT? Vill du forma innovativa och smarta IT-lösningar i agila team som skapar trygghet och värde för våra kunder? Just nu fokuserar vi på digitalisering av kundmötet, utveckling av morgondagens försäkringssystem och förflyttning mot publika molntjänster.
Datadomänen växer och vi ser nu behov av att utöka med ytterligare en Product Owner med god teknisk förståelse som vill vara med på vår molnresa.
Det här gör du som Product Owner på Folksam
Som PO inom datadomänen arbetar du med i stort sett hela Folksam. Du har många kontaktytor, vilket innebär att du behöver ha en god kommunikativ förmåga och vara bekväm med att kommunicera på olika nivåer. Du arbetar dagligen nära utvecklingsteamet, Scrum Master, andra Product Owners såväl som Product Manager.
Dina huvudsakliga arbetsuppgifter är att:
Baserat på våra kunders behov och ta fram en produktbacklog och tillhörande roadmap genom hela produktens livscykel.
Balansera backlog med ett helhetsperspektiv inkluderande risker, förvaltning, kostnad och nya möjligheter.
Fungera som kontaktpunkt från kunderna in till teamet/avdelningen.
Delta och vara drivande i samverkansmöten såväl inom teamet som i tågets ART-ceremonier.
Aktivt bidra till att utmana våra kunder/beställare för att löpande förbättra arbetssätt och strukturer.
Samarbeta, rapportera och kommunicera både internt och externt.
Är du den vi söker?
I rollen som Product Owner är det viktigt att du har förmågan att etablera en produktvision och inspirera teamet. Med andra ord är dina kommunikativa förmågor av hög vikt. Du trivs med att fatta beslut och är bekväm med att avväga när kortsiktiga respektive långsiktiga lösningar bör tillämpas. För att vara framgångsrik i denna roll tror vi att du har en teknisk bakgrund och gärna inom området data och analys.
Utvecklas tillsammans med oss
Folksam är ett kundägt företag med stort fokus på hållbarhetsfrågor. Vi har många roliga, utvecklande jobb och bra förmåner. Vi tror på ett hållbart arbetsliv och hos oss har du goda chanser till en spännande karriär. Vi erbjuder flexibilitet att varva arbete på kontoret och hemifrån utifrån verksamhetens behov. Våra trevliga kontor runt om i landet ger mötesplatser för samarbete, lärande och en gemensam kultur – tillsammans skapar vi engagemang och kraft framåt! På folksam.se/jobb-och-karriar kan du läsa mer och se filmer om hur det är att jobba på Folksam.
Så söker du jobbet
Välkommen att skicka in din ansökan redan idag, men senast 13 februari 2023. Intervjuer sker löpande under ansökningstiden.
Vill du veta mer om jobbet är du välkommen att kontakta någon av rekryterande cheferna Jacob Karmehag, 072-468 71 83, jacob.karmehag@folksam.se eller Henrik Nose, 070-831 52 82, henrik.nose@folksam.se
Fackliga representanter: Akademikerföreningen Per Hansson 070-831 60 67, Forena Morgan Svensson 073-423 59 12 och Handels Mikael Carlsson 070-831 51 32.
Folksamgruppen erbjuder försäkringar och långsiktigt sparande som skapar trygghet i livets alla skeden. Vi är cirka 4 000 medarbetare och vår vision är att våra kunder ska känna sig trygga i en hållbar värld. Vi engagerar oss i det våra kunder bryr sig om och är måna om att de är rätt försäkrade.

Title: Data & Analytics Leader, Customer selling & payments Group, Digital, INGKA Group
Description:
Who you are

We are looking for a people-centric leader, with strong technical expertise, to co-drive our product roadmap for IKEA. As a person, you are passionate about leading business, and building and developing a strong team of data analysts. Ideally, you have experience working as a technical lead, consultant and/or as a people manager within the Data & Analytics space.

You like solving difficult business problems with data and analytics, working with state-of-the-art technologies, and working with people. All this while you solve real problems for IKEA customers and co-workers.

You are an analytics practitioner with an extensive background in data analysis and 5+ years of experience in leading teams.

This leadership role will work with creating opportunities and solving customer pains with data and analytics, joining a diverse team within Data & Analytics consisting of data analysts, data scientists, data engineers, ML engineers and data stewards based across Sweden, the Netherlands and Spain.

You are an expert when it comes to:

modern methods for extracting insights and making decisions based on data
relevant programming languages (such as SQL, Python), as well as industrial usage of modern cloud
platforms for data processing and analysis data storytelling on both hyper-scaled sales and payment data as well as web
analytics data
digital product development, with a strong appreciation for the importance of rapid validated learning cycles for optimizing
performance long term

Your past experiences include:

formal qualifications (BSc, MSc, PhD) in computer science, econometrics, engineering, mathematics, or equivalent
diverse professional experience in working with data and analytics
demonstrable experience working in Agile or DevOps communities of engineering practice
leading change in a large organization
building a team, recruiting and developing world-class team members

Our values underpin and guide us in our everyday work life. For you to thrive and grow with IKEA, it is important for us that you share and lead with our values at heart.

Your responsibilities

As a Data & Analytics Leader for Selling and Payment area within The Customer Domain, you will lead a world-class team, with direct responsibility for driving business value, as well as managing people processes, incl. ensuring the health and well-being of your team. You will be responsible for improving data-driven decision-making and actively bringing analytics into our product strategy work by focusing on Product Insights

The mission of the Customer Domain is to provide a convenient, inspiring, and fun shopping experience to the many customers of IKEA. IKEA generates massive amounts of data and unlocking the value from this data is the foundation for achieving the mission. Your role will include deriving insights into customer behavior and preferences, delivering advanced analytics use cases and enabling others to get value from our data.

As part of a cross-functional leadership team, you will work collaboratively with Product, Tech, and UX Design leaders to inspire and empower product teams and ensure that we attain our desired business objectives (OKRs). In addition, you will work closely with key data and technology enablement units, incl. Data Architecture, to secure coherent, effective product development across the organization.

Our team within Ikea

In Group Digital, we set the agenda to keep IKEA leading in an uncertain and fast-moving environment. We drive the development, provision and operation of our digital products and services using existing and emerging new technologies and agile delivery methods to deliver at pace. At the same time, we provide a home to develop and extend the business, people, and technical skills needed to ensure continuous improvement and growth of our digital capability. We are a global team, focused on building global solutions, thinking scale into everything we do.

We offer:

an exciting, empowering work environment with exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us
flexible and modern tools to benefit and learn from (incl. GCP for processing data and deploying machine learning models)
a world-class Data & Analytics community with colleagues from diverse academia and industry backgrounds and high
ambitions
the opportunity to join a truly value-based company, in which laughter, openness and mutual trust is the norm

Questions and support? Let's connect!

In this role, you will report to Data & Analytics Selling and Payment Area Manager in Customer Domain. The role is based in Malmö, Madrid or Amsterdam. If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please reach out to Annette Björkquist-Åhstedt (annette.bjorkquist-ahstedt @ ingka.ikea.com).

Please apply with your application in English. Note that we cannot process any applications through e-mail.

Looking forward to reading your applications!

Title: Production Data Analyst [Production Intelligence]
Description:
Job Description

As a Production Data Analyst at Massive, you work with extracting, visualizing, monitoring and analyzing production related data, with the purpose of providing visibility and predictability of our game productions which in turn allows our producers to make data informed decisions, measure progress, mitigate risks, plan ahead and improve the way we make games.
In this role you will work with several different data sources, ranging from HR and financial data to data from our project tracking software, version control software and build pipeline.
As a Production Data Analyst you will work closely with the Production Directors on the game projects, who are the primary customer of this data, understanding their needs and assisting them with interpreting the data and providing them with insights. You will also work closely with Production Transformation, who strives to continuously improve the Studio’s production methods. This position reports directly to the Studio Production Strategy Director.
This is a permanent position based in Malmö Sweden, with the opportunity to work partially from home according to our Flexible Workplace Policy. Please apply in English (our company language), and we’ll check your application asap!
What you’ll do
You implement, visualize, monitor and analyze production data and KPIs, and provide insights and guidance to the production teams based on this data.
Together with the producers on the game projects, identify what KPIs and data visualizations are needed to improve visibility and predictability of the production.
Define how data and insights will be reported and ensure the delivery and relevance of the reporting throughout the production period.
Providing ongoing data informed production risk assessment, flagging trends and KPIs that are off target.
International travel required.

Qualifications

What you’ll bring
You are curious and have a passion for building easily accessible data visualizations that can be intuitively understood. You are well oriented in how software production works, and thrive working close to the daily challenges of production. You have solid communication skills and feel comfortable presenting your findings to an audience, explaining complex information simply and clearly. You are passionate about detail, math, statistics and data technologies. Besides the above we’re looking for someone aligned with our core values and the following skills and experience:
Degree in one of the following areas: Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, Business Analytics, or relevant professional experience
Solid experience in data analytics or business analytics.
You have a passion for detail, math and statistics in general.
Strong communication skills is a must.
Excellent skills with data visualization tools (ex: Tableau, PowerBI)
Proficient in writing complex SQL queries.
Is a bonus if you:
Have previous experience of video game production
Have previous experience of financial analysis

Additional Information

Massive Entertainment is a world-leading AAA studio located in Malmö Sweden and is part of the Ubisoft family. We’re a multinational team of more than 750 passionate and highly skilled people from 50+ different countries. Our studio’s goal has always been – and still is – to craft the finest gaming experiences for all players.
At Massive, you get to do what you love most while bringing your own experience to our ongoing projects, like Tom Clancy’s The Division 2, Avatar: Frontiers of Pandora, and The Star Wars Project. We're also developing new tech here, such as our in-house engine Snowdrop, and Ubisoft Connect - Ubisoft's digital ecosystem and distribution platform.
All your application information will be kept confidential according to EEO & GDPR guidelines.

Nu söker vi fler fantastiska kollegor till vårt team som

Title: Data Science Lead
Description:
JOIN THE KODIAK HUB SLEUTH AS WE AID GLOBAL COMPANIES TO CREATE SMARTER & MORE SUSTAINABLE SUPPLY CHAINS AT SCALE.
Ready to work with something that creates real impact? Check out our opening

Who we are?

Kodiak Hub is a growth venture offering SaaS solutions engineered to revolutionize Supplier Relationship Management (SRM). We are building the next generation of B2B SaaS, based on business intelligence, automation, big data analytics, and machine learning technology, creating a blueprint of how companies optimize their interaction and collaboration with suppliers.

Our team is international and tight-knit, composed of competent and creative individuals. We double our revenue on a yearly basis, and we have an aggressive yet realistic growth model for the following years. As our product is completely novel, we are constantly figuring out innovative solutions to the market's challenges.

Join us and help us change the way companies operate in their global supply chains!

We have an opening for a Data Science Lead!

We are looking for an energetic, engaged Data Science Lead who aspires to improve the world!

As our Data Science Lead, you will be responsible for analyzing the current data from the platform, visualizing and explaining data insights to drive decision-making, both internally and externally, executing AI, machine learning, and data analysis projects, advising about the data architecture and training internal and external stakeholders.

Candidates' Requirements Attributes:
Data analyst, engineer, or scientist degree.
Proficiency in statistical models
Machine Learning skills are a must
Proficiency in Python, Pandas, NumPy, etc., is a must
Proficiency in Excel is a must
Tableau and/or Power BI is a plus
R is a plus
Excellent proficiency in English, both verbally and written

Title: Data & Analytics Leader – Order Management Group Digital, Ingka Group
Description:
Who you are

We are looking for a technical and people centric leader with focus on creating tangible value from data, analytics and data-driven decision making. This includes building digital products based on Advanced Analytics, as well as driving enabling processes such as Data Engineering and Data Stewardship. As a person you are passionate about leading business areas, influencing stakeholders, coaching, developing, and building a team. It is likely that you are currently working as a technical lead or having people responsibility in the Data & Analytics space. You are motivated to stay up to date on the latest developments, tools and technologies of the rapidly changing data and analytics landscape.

Our strong IKEA values are underpinning and guiding us in our everyday work life, in discussions, decisions and activities. For you to thrive and grow with IKEA it’s important for us that you share and lead with our values!

You have good knowledge in the following areas:
Application of advanced analytics and data analytics in addressing and solving business problems
Analytical reporting, data engineering, insights generation, machine learning and a broad understanding of the developments in the fast-moving data technology landscape
Programming languages, modern platforms, and systems for handling small and large datasets
Data models and common issues related to data quality, and how to improve them
Data-driven digital product development, including data processing, analysis, and knowledge extraction, with agile processes, continuous improvement, and deployment at scale
Stakeholder management, in relation to development of data-driven digital products

Your qualifications and past experiences are:
Diverse hands-on experience in professional data and analytics work
Leading and developing a team
Formal advanced education in engineering, computer science, econometrics, mathematics, operations research or equivalent
Demonstrable experience in working in an Agile or DevOps environment
Experience of driving change in an organization
Experience in product or analytics development for retail is a plus
Experience of working with (advanced) analytics on logistics/supply chain or related topics is a plus

Your responsibilities

You will be the line manager for a team of Data & Analytics professionals with responsibility for driving value creation from data and analytics, as well as for people processes such as recruitment, performance, competence, career development and health/welfare of co-workers.

Specifically, you and your team will be embedded in the order management area of our Fulfilment domain. Here, we are building the systems and data-driven decision support tools that underpin and optimize the end-to-end lifecycle of our customer orders. In our journey towards an omnichannel retailer, this domain is critical for our business.

As part of a cross-functional leadership team, you will work collaboratively with Product Managers, Engineering Managers and UX Design leaders to inspire and empower teams, shape product roadmaps, and enable achievement of desired business outcomes. Within the Data & Analytics community you will support management with strategic, tactical, and technical input. You will also work closely with key data enablement units like Data Management and Data Architecture to secure successful data-driven product development.

Within your assigned area of Order Management, you are responsible for:
guiding and advising on the implementation and application of Data & Analytics solutions within product team(s), for example to provide insights into delivery operations or develop algorithms to find the best way to automatically handle order deviations
actively striving to improve our business with data-driven insights and decision-making solutions, going beyond delivering regular reporting and dashboards
building your team and ensuring the right Data & Analytics resources, people and expertise are available for committed product development
promoting effectiveness and best practices in Data & Analytics – continually benchmarking against industry standards and trends
ensuring that all order data is captured, stored, and shared in a way that is technically robust, compliant with both legal requirements and IKEA policies, cost-effective, and easy-to-use for improving the business

Our team within Ikea

At Group Digital, we set the digital agenda to keep IKEA leading in an uncertain and fast-moving environment. We drive the development, provision and operation of our digital products and services using existing and emerging modern technologies and agile delivery methods to deliver at pace. At the same time, we provide a home to develop and extend the business, people, and technical skills needed to ensure continuous improvement and growth of our digital capability. We are a global team and work together on global solutions.

The Data & Analytics function is a core pillar of Group Digital, with responsibility to shape and drive digital objectives with deep internal competence along the data value chain, ranging from key enablers such as Data Management and Data Architecture to product success drivers like Data Engineering and Advanced Analytics.

We can offer you:
An exciting and empowering work environment with exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us
Opportunities to have tremendous and global impact with your work
Flexible and modern tools: we deploy on Google Cloud Platform, and we use a lot of open-source solutions across the board
Hardware and OS of your choice
A team of great colleagues to learn with and from (with world-class experience across all aspects of Data & Analytics)
Flexible and friendly working environment in a truly value-based company

Questions and support? Let's connect!

The role is based in Helsingborg or Malmö, Sweden – with a hybrid work environment.

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please reach out to Carl-Johan Andersson at carl-johan.andersson@ingka.ikea.com . Please apply with your application in English. Note that we cannot process any applications through e-mail.

A background check will be part of the recruitment process for the final candidate.

Title: Business Development Representative - Data Analytics
Description:
Transforming the Future with the Convergence of Simulation and Data
Business Development Representative – Data Analytics SaaS Nordics
Lund, Sweden
Do you like a challenge, are you a complex thinker who likes to solve problems? If so, then you might be the new Altairian we are searching for. At Altair, your curiosity matters. We pride ourselves on a business culture that enables open, creative thinking, and we deeply value our employees and their contributions towards our clients' success, as well as our own.

Job Summary:
The Altair Data Analytics team is looking for a Business Development Representative to help generate new business. This is an exciting opportunity to work in a growing company currently developing new technology.
Altair offers a highly advanced and powerful data analytics solution for businesses in the areas of data preparation, data science, and data visualisation. Our customers use our products to solve their business problems, and generate deeper insight from their data, resulting in increased efficiency and profitability.

BDRs are responsible for proactive inbound/outbound prospecting, lead/contact management and pipeline building. This position will have a direct impact on our success by providing qualified prospects to AE’s for Opportunity creation. As a member of the BDR Team you will be joining a fast-paced close nit group that thrive in a competitive environment. You will partner with AE’s across the organisation to create new selling opportunities in key targeted accounts across multiple industry verticals.
In this role, you will be provided the guidance and training needed to become a technology sales expert while mastering the art of the cold call and the finesse of targeted email campaigns. You will actively collaborate with marketing and sales executives to develop the best ways to grow the AE’s Pipeline. If you are looking to master your sales skills, grow as a sales professional and launch your sales career, this is the opportunity for you.

What You Will Need:
Basics:
If you have at least 1-2 years’ experience in a sales role (or similar) where you can demonstrate successes and wins as well as fluency in one of the Scandinavian languages, (Swedish, Norwegian or Danish) or Finnish, and English, you could be our next Altairian! We also value software sales experience as well as enterprise and financial services industry knowledge.
Ideally, you will have experience in the following areas:
Lead generation & qualification
Account mapping
Campaign building
Working internationally (Nordic territory)
Cold calling, 40+ calls a day
CRM, Microsoft Office

How You Will Be Successful:
Envision the Future
Communicate Honestly and Broadly
Seek Technology and Business “Firsts”
Embrace Diversity and Take Risks

What We Offer:
Work actively for employeés health/wellness
High team spirit
Smaller companies locally but part of a global group
Unique expert knowledge
Hybrid working model
Competitive salary

Why Work with Us:
Altair is a global technology company providing software and cloud solutions in the areas of product development, high-performance computing (HPC) and artificial intelligence (AI). Altair enables organizations in nearly every industry to compete more effectively in a connected world, while creating a more sustainable future. With more than 3,000 engineers, scientists and creative thinkers in 25 countries, we help solve our customer’s toughest challenges and deliver unparalleled service, helping the innovators innovate, drive better decisions, and turn today’s problems into tomorrow’s opportunities.

Our vision is to transform customer decision making with data analytics, simulation, and high-performance computing and artificial intelligence (AI).
For more than 30 years, we have been helping our customers integrate electronics and controls with mechanical design to expand product value, develop AI, simulation and data-driven digital twins to drive better decisions, and deliver advanced HPC and cloud solutions to support unlimited idea exploration.

Ready to go? #ONLYFORWARD
At our core we are explorers; adventurers; pioneers. We are the brains behind some of the world’s most revolutionary innovations and are not only comfortable in new and uncharted waters, we dive in headfirst. We are the original trailblazers that make the impossible possible; discovering new solutions to our customer’s toughest challenges.
Altair is an equal opportunity employer. Our backgrounds are diverse, and every member of our global team is critical to our success. Altair's history demonstrates a belief that empowering each individual authentic voice reinforces a culture that thrives because of the uniqueness among our team.

Title: Future Talent Programme - Analyst Business Information & Analytics
Description:
At Tetra Pak we commit to making food safe and available, everywhere; and we protect what's good – protecting food, protecting people, and protecting the planet. By doing so we touch millions of people's lives every day. And we need people like you to make it happen.
Job Summary
Start your career development and become Tetra Pak’s next Future Talent! We are looking for highly motivated newly graduates to join us in 2023!

Future Talent Program is a Trainee Program within Tetra Pak. We offer a permanent position from start in September 2023 at our site in Lund. You will onboard an individual designed development program for 18 months connected to a specific position and the Tetra Pak organization. During the program you will participate in trainings and job rotations throughout various parts of Tetra Pak to explore your potential and grow as a person. As a Trainee here with us, you will get to know our entire business and collaborate with colleagues all over the world. And this is just the beginning of your Tetra Pak career!

Visit https://www.tetrapak.com/about/future-talent and read more about Tetra Pak Future Talent Program!

You will be based in Lund, Sweden but you will work in a global arena.
What you will do
As our new Future Talent – Analyst Business Information & Analytics you will:
Be part of Business Information & Analytics (BI&A) Center of Excellence (COE) coordinating BI&A activities in all geographies and business units
Contribute to defining Tetra Pak BI&A strategy and driving it implementation in the lines of business
Collaborate with various networks of Colleagues to deploy BI&A solutions
Learn best in class BI&A tools (Microsoft Power BI, KNIME, SAP HANA…) and transfer your knowledge to Tetra Pak Colleagues
Facilitate interactions between IT and Business
Roll-out of Data Science capabilities to business users
We believe you have
You have a Masters Degree in Computer Science/Engineering, Data Analytics and Business Economics, or Information Systems (Graduated 2022-2023)
It is possible that you have experience working in multi-cultural environment, proven to be independent self-learner.
You are fluent in English, written and spoken.
You have good communications skills, written and spoken
Previous international studies/experience are considered meritious
We Offer You
A variety of exciting challenges with ample opportunities for development and training in a truly global landscape
A culture that pioneers a spirit of innovation where our industry experts drive visible results
An equal opportunity employment experience that values diversity and inclusion
Market competitive compensation and benefits with flexible working arrangements

Apply Now
If you are inspired to be part of our promise to protect what’s good; for food, people, and the planet, apply with your CV and Cover Letter through our careers page at https://jobs.tetrapak.com/.

This job posting expires on 2023-02-01
