Questions about your application contact Josephine Malalla at +46 46 36 5253
For trade union information contact Sveriges Ingenörer Lars Haraldsson at +46 46 36 2533 and Unionen Lisbeth Larsson e at +46 46 36 2320

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
What is ArK?
There are many consumer facing fintech products, but finance as a whole is virtually untouched by technology. Investment decisions are still being made off of pdf’s and “shark tank”-like processes rather than utilising the forecasting methods found at companies like Spotify or Google. This makes capital allocation riddled with bias and very ripe for disruption. At ArK we’re convinced that by putting data and tech at the heart of finance we can impact how money flows and, in turn, create a more democratised and unbiased economy.
Today we offer founders access to our machine learning platform AIM. Through connecting their raw data we can fully understand what they’ve built without any bias; connecting what has been achieved historically into a simulated 5-year future. This prediction is the foundation for the transformational loans that we are able to issue, and a tool that founders get to keep for business optimisation.
ArK was founded in 2021 by a six-time entrepreneur, a world-class AI technology developer and a veteran banker. Since then we’ve carefully grown our team to 30 - all pitching in with their experience to build something that none of us has seen before. ArK is headquartered in Stockholm but we balance our time between being at the office and working remotely.
Data Analyst
As a data analyst at ArK, you will be working closely with our data scientists, commercial teams, engineering and design. Your goal is to ensure we are able to make the best credit decisions in the world, and that we do so in an increasingly scalable and automated way.
Together we build AIM, our analytics platform, that not only helps us develop financial products, but is also turning into an amazing tool for founders of growth companies to use.
In other words, the analysis we do isn’t kept to ourselves, but something we share interactive access to with our customers. Data Analysts at ArK develop the insights that we package there, and the vision is to give its users an unfair competitive advantage.
Who are you?
Someone who enjoys learning new things and tools, and who enjoys pushing themselves and others to grow
You likely have an economics or STEM background, but we really value broad perspectives, so if you come from elsewhere but have an inclination for data, tech or business — you’re more than welcome to apply
A few years hands-on experience with modern data analytics, using tools like SQL, dbt, Python, R and probably some dashboarding solution.
Nice-to-have
A good understanding of statistics and advanced data modelling
Experience running projects and collaborating with external stakeholders
Experience setting up KPIs and understanding their drivers
An interest in business and what makes (some) companies succeed
What’s it like to work at ArK?
We believe that the key to a great team culture is great people having a great time together. Our unique combination of startup mentality, experienced team and ambitious vision make room for possibilities to grow into leadership roles, either going deep into tech or towards people management (or why not both!).

Title: Senior Analytics Manager
Description:
At Storytel we believe that powerful stories add an extra dimension to life.
Storytel is one of the world’s leading audiobook and ebook streaming services and we offer unlimited listening to consumers in 25+ markets.
Our vision is to make the world a more empathetic place with great stories to be shared and enjoyed by anyone, anywhere, anytime

About the Role
As a Senior Analytics Manager, you will be responsible for leading a growing team of analysts in the scoping and execution of data and analytics projects that support the product strategy and the successful growth of the company. You will develop analytical solutions powered by a modern data stack in a dynamic environment where you will have the opportunity to directly impact how we work with data across the organization. You will, over time, shape the team and capabilities towards a truly federated operational model for analytics.
If you're a data-driven, empathic leader with strong communication skills and a passion for driving positive change through data-driven decision making, you would be a great fit for our team. Join us and play a key role in driving the growth of one of the world's leading audiobook and ebook streaming services.

What you’ll do
Lead, manage and grow a team of data analysts
Support the team to drive impact by prioritizing projects with highest business opportunity and/or of long term strategic importance while managing stakeholders expectations
Mentor the team on data & analytics technical skills, career development and stakeholder management
Collaborate closely with and influence business and product staff and leaders as part of multidisciplinary teams to assess analytics opportunities and develop data and analytics products and solutions
Partner closely with peers and stakeholders within the data science engineering domain, broader engineering and product to support the successful end-to-end delivery of analyses and solutions
Continuously collaborate with stakeholders to ensure data insights and solutions are incorporated in a day-to-day decision making, OKR planning and strategic prioritization
Work closely with the data engineering team to support our efforts in delivering self service analytics solutions, appropriate data pipelines and documentation and capabilities to the community of analytics users
Support Storytel’s efforts in becoming a data-led organization through capability building, adoption of new tooling, data literacy initiatives and supporting teams develop a data-first mindset in their workflows

About You
To succeed in this role, we believe that:
You have a background in a quantitative discipline such as Computer Science, Engineering, Information Science, Statistics or a related field
You have 7+ years of experience in analytics
You have several years of hands-on experience in SQL, R, Python and data visualization tools
You have few years of experience in directly managing data analytics team
You are an empathic leader, who enjoys mentoring and coaching others You are highly adaptable and can successfully uncover and navigate greenfield analytics projects
You have a deep interest and enthusiasm for working with data and are highly motivated to drive positive change in organizations through data-driven decision making
You have strong communication skills to partner with stakeholders effectively and are able to successfully bridge with non-technical audiences

Bonus if you have one or more of the following:
Advanced relevant degree
Experience in analytics management from product and/or growth companies
Hands-on modeling experience (statistical modeling, forecasting, A/B testing, etc)
Experience with the modern data stack and cloud technologies Experience with experimentation frameworks and platforms

What we offer
At Storytel we trust our employees and believe in their autonomy. We offer flexible working hours, remote working possibilities when possible and flexible public holidays for people to celebrate what they truly believe in.
Storytel’s culture encourages self-leadership, innovation, collaboration – and our employees share a common passion for high-quality content and stories. There is a strong emphasis on continuous development, learning through experimentation and actively sharing feedback to constantly improve performance.
Storytel offers a friendly, entrepreneurial and fast-moving work environment where new ideas and creativity are welcomed. We like doing things in new ways and questioning old methods. The Storytel culture - characterized by being welcoming and helpful - is important to us. We don’t believe in hierarchy and micromanagement; we highly believe in giving responsibility and having people grow alongside it. And of course - you get unlimited listening to audio and ebooks from our service!
Does this sound like you? If you feel like Storytel is a place where you could thrive, please submit your application in English and we will contact you as soon as possible.

Title: Ledare inom Data & Analytics
Description:
Till vårt trevliga Malmökontor söker vi dig som vill bli en nyckelperson i att vara med och vidareutveckla vår Data och Analytics-drivna verksamhet och affär. Vi hoppas hitta dig som vill hjälpa våra kunder med sin digitala resa. I gengäld erbjuds du ett jobb hos en av Sveriges bästa arbetsgivare (enligt Great Place To Work) i en roll där trygghet och flexibilitet förenas. Hos oss på Sopra Steria sitter kunskapsdelning i väggarna och är en av ingredienserna till att vi har kul på jobbet - vi kallar det Power of Sharing!
Om tjänsten
Tjänsten innebär att i rollen som Personnel Manager (PM) ansvara för ett team på 8–12 medarbetare. Rollen är bred och omväxlande där ditt uppdrag blir att leda och inspirera ditt team till nya mål parallellt om du själv kan utvecklas genom egna konsultuppdrag (på max 50%). Dina dagar kommer dessutom att innehålla aktiviteter inom sälj, marknad samt affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling. Med denna breda erfarenhetsbas har du givetvis en också en plats i Data & Analytics-enhetens svenska ledningsgrupp.
Data & Analytics består idag av ett 50-tal erfarna stjärnor runt Sverige och tillsammans använder vi våra kompetenser och förmågor till att skapa värde åt våra kunder utifrån deras data. Enheten har gedigen kompetens inom allt ifrån klassisk data warehouseing och BI-verktyg till machine learning och avancerad analys.
Vem är du?
Då rollen är bred söker vi dig som redan har hunnit inhämta olika typer av erfarenhet som du nu kan ösa ur. Vi tänker oss att du har några års erfarenhet av ledarskap samt ”hands on”-erfarenhet inom minst ett av områdena data engineering, avancerad analys, projektledning och datastrategi. Du behöver även ha jobbat inom minst ett av områdena affärsutveckling, sälj, kundansvar eller liknande. För att trivas i vår miljö är det såklart också en fördel om gillar att jobba med teknik i framkant!
Svenska och engelska på professionell nivå behövs för den här tjänsten.
Mer om oss
Att arbeta på Sopra Steria innebär att tillhöra ”A place to Grow”. Vi är nämligen övertygade om att när vi kan växa som individer växer vi också som företag. Som konsult hos oss kommer du att ställas inför nya problem, tekniker, processer, roller och perspektiv som ger dig nya erfarenheter och värdefulla insikter. Genom vår starka delningskultur ”Power of Sharing” utvecklar vi sedan varandra, våra kunder och samhället i stort. En kultur att vara stolt över!
Sopra Steria är ett internationellt konsultföretag som är ledande inom digital transformation av medelstora och stora organisationer. Vår unika kombination av specialistkompetens inom både verksamhetsutveckling och IT ökar värdet på och användbarheten av våra kunders satsningar. I världen är vi mer än 47 000 medarbetare. Strax under 500 av oss finns här i Sverige, där var tredje medarbetare är en kvinna. Vår starka kultur bygger på samverkan och teamwork.
Sopra Steria rankas av Gartner som ett topp 5 bolag i Europa inom Digital Transformation
Ansökan
Nu vill vi gärna höra lite om dig! Ansök enkelt genom att antingen ladda upp ditt CV eller länka direkt till ditt LinkedIn-konto via annonsen på vår hemsida! Om det fortfarande finns något du funderar över är du välkommen att kontakta Jan Svanholt: jan.svanholt@soprasteria.com.
Vi ser fram emot att få höra ifrån dig!

Title: Konsult inom Data Analytics
Description:
Hösten 2020 startade vi upp ett nytt team inom området Data Analytics i Skåne. Vi sitter centralt i Malmö och har även ett kontor i Kristianstad och är ett team med bra mix av människor och erfarenheter. Nu är vi en tillväxtfas som går snabbt och söker fler engagerade konsulter som vill vara med och utveckla verksamheten och leverera XLENTa lösningar till våra kunder tillsammans med oss!
Vad letar vi efter?
Vi söker allt från juniora till erfarna personer som har berört något av områdena nedan:
Business Intelligence – Från Frontend till Backend med tekniker som Power BI, DAX, SSRS, SSAS, Azure, SQL, Datawarehouse, SQL Server, Qlik mfl.
Performance Management (CPM) – IBM Planning Analtyics, Jedox
Vi erbjuder intressanta projekt där vi gör allt från att utveckla till att implementera hållbara och smarta lösningar till våra kunder inom både privat och offentlig sektor.
Om oss
Vi är ett glatt och drivet gäng som har kul på jobbet, framåtriktade med lång erfarenhet inom Data Analytics som är i starten på en spännande resa, där alla hjälps åt att påverka både sin egen och bolagets utveckling.
Vi är en del av Xlent Consulting Group med hundratals duktiga konsulter över hela Sverige (och lite i Norge). Detta gör att vi kombinerar det lilla företagets fördelar med styrkan hos en större organisation.

Title: Qlik Sense developer and Data Analyst
Description:
Job brief
We are looking for a passionate Data Analyst. The successful candidate will turn data into information, information into insight and insight into business decisions.

Job Duties
The Data analyst will be developing and maintaining Qlik Sense applications based on requirements of the business, building and managing data source libraries, and help develop the usage within the organisation. They will also monitor performance and quality control plans to identify improvements.

Responsibilities
Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets
Design and maintain data model structure
Develop and implement BI applications for reporting and data analytics that optimize efficiency and quality
Acquire, and manage, data from primary or secondary data sources
Train end-users on new reports and dashboards
Provide quality assurance of imported data
Work with management to prioritize business and information needs
Locate and define new process improvement opportunities

Requirements
Proven working experience as a Data Analyst or Business Data Analyst
+3 years experience of QlikView or Qlik Sense
Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques
Strong knowledge of and experience with reporting packages (Business Objects etc), databases (SQL etc), programming (XML, Javascript, or ETL frameworks)
Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (Excel, SPSS, SAS etc)
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy
Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings
BS in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management or Statistics
Ability to work with stakeholders to assess potential risks
Ability to translate business requirements into non-technical, lay terms
High level written and verbal communication skills
We also want you to live our core values:
innovate
be curious
have fun
work smart
take responsibility
#LI-TB1

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Ingrid is hiring! Our Data & Analytics team is growing team is growing—are you our new Data Analyst?
Ingrid is on a mission to solve the largest problem with global e-commerce and create the world’s best delivery experiences.
Ingrid provides consumers with a much better shopping experience through intelligent choice of delivery options and flexible last mile deliveries—on their own terms. Our key objective is to increase merchant credibility and consumer convenience. We have successfully done so since 2015. By integrating Ingrid’s SaaS-platform, e-commerce merchants are able to improve online shopping experiences for all consumers and any purchase.
We’re the best at what we do and always looking to hire the best people around.

About the role
As a data analyst you will be part of Ingrid’s Data & Analytics team which is responsible for enabling Ingrid teams and customers with data insights. Your primary focus will be to support the product team and help them to understand how our products are performing and how they can be further improved by using data insights. This role requires that you’re curious to know how a product works behind the scenes but also what’s making the customer enjoy the product. We believe that you love working with huge amounts of data in a complex environment where you see the opportunity to further improve your skills within the data & analytics space.

Examples of responsibilities within this role:
Build a strong understanding of Ingrid products and the data underlying them.
Proactively analyze performance of Ingrid’s products and help drive product development using data.
Maintain and develop new metrics related to Ingrid products
Refine existing curated data layers as well as developing new ones.
Contribute to the data & analytics team overall structure.

About you
You have 1-2 years of experience in the data & analytics space
You have completed a degree in statistics, mathematics, economics, computer science or an equivalent education or possess relevant practical experience
You have solid experience with SQL (BigQuery or similar is a plus)
You have experience in visualizing and communicating insights from data (Metabase or similar is a plus)
You have very good communication skills in English, both written and oral

Meritorious
Previous experience working with product analytics
Experience with statistical programming tools such as Python or R.
A/B testing experience (designing experiments and analyzing results).
Experience working with Git and analytics engineering tools such as DBT.

What we offer:
Flexible cooperation and a unique, informal atmosphere
The opportunity to develop your skills and gain experience by working with strong international brands on innovative projects
Support from experienced team members
Experiencing great teamwork at a highly ambitious startup

Title: Team Lead - Analytics & Data Science
Description:
Why Avaus?
We are the leading marketing and sales transformation partner in the Nordics! We are 120 colleagues located at our offices in Helsinki, Stockholm, Munich, Milan and Gdansk. As a company, we have more than 15 years of experience in data-driven marketing and sales in large organizations across B2C & B2B industries.
Our vision is to become the leading actionable marketing data-asset provider in Europe by 2025. We believe that to survive, companies need to invest heavily in capabilities related to intelligence & AI, customer experience, personalisation and change management. Our mission is to foster customer-centric organizations equipped to grow and face the future. Our own future growth is heavily driven by activating data and analytics for our clients.
The Team
The Analytics team at Avaus consists of data scientists, BI & CRM analysts, and is a team of highly skilled and ambitious people, eager to improve our clients’ results by providing them with better decisions and actions based on data. We work in a wide range of tools and languages to orchestrate and automate the activation of customer data. We are a social crew and enjoy working closely together and learning from one another.


The role
As the Team Lead for our Analytics team, you will be responsible for managing team development plans, coach and guide team members and assist our operations matching the right person for projects. You will also be responsible for the team's career development, recruitment, resourcing and establishing a culture in line with Avaus cultural cornerstones. As a team lead you will need to be a trusted role model for your team and among your peers. Apart from leading your team, you’re also expected to act as a subject-matter expert in client projects. You will most likely be doing some of these things also:
People & team management
Performance reviews and dito assessments, including salary reviews
Coaching of individuals and teams
Personal & career development plans and execution
Competence area customer delivery and subject matter expertise
Team building
Operations & resourcing
Contribute to sales cases within competence area
1-1:s and individual follow-up
Participate in building a growth mindset and culture within the organization
Thought-leadership around the selected topic, both internally and externally


Who are you?
For this role, we are primarily looking for someone with strong leadership skills. It’s preferable if you have experience within marketing automation, CRM Marketing, Content automation and consulting in general. The role will also include supporting client projects and helping clients define and execute on personalization strategies.
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree within a relevant field
Multiple years of relevant work experience, preferably within consulting
Consultancy mindset and the ability to work in fast paced environments
Proven track record within people and team leadership
Extensive experience in data, analytics and reporting
Fluent in Swedish, as our customers require us to communicate in Swedish
Fluent in English
Practical information
This is a permanent position with a 6 months’ probation period, based at our Stockholm office at Katarinavägen 17. Starting date as soon as possible or by agreement. We offer a hybrid remote workplace and you will report to Head of Delivery.
Already feel like one of us? Send your applications in English as soon as possible, but no later than 2023-02-28. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Paola Banegas, Head of Talant. Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page.
We look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
About Froda
Froda was founded in 2015 with a clear vision – to revolutionize the banking experience for entrepreneurs by making it easy and affordable for them to invest in their ideas. Today, we are one of Sweden's fastest growing fintech with major international growth plans. We are a creative tech company with the ambition to turn a historically expensive and unfair industry into something ethical, sustainable, and forward thinking. Behind the company are several well-known investors and talents from e.g., Avanza, Spotify, Google, and Klarna.

About the Role
Froda is at the unique point of taking our data analytics and real-time decisioning to the next level. We are now looking for our next Data Scientist to help us transform our data into actionable insights.

You will design, develop, and maintain statistical data models in collaboration with our chief data scientist as well as our data engineers and analysts. Besides working with modeling you will also build and work on the data pipelines which feed our models.

This is a key role in evolving Froda's data strategy as well as in the development and realization of our data platform.

Who are you?
We believe that you are a curious person who enjoys working in a team with other eager and open-minded people, who can’t wait to learn more and share their knowledge. You are driven by finding the right solution, in a business-oriented manner. We want you to be fluent in English and Swedish for this role, and to have a master's degree preferably in engineering, mathematics, or statistical modeling.
When it comes to your tech skills, we believe that you have experience of:
At least a couple of years as a Data Scientist or a similar role,
Working with statistical modeling in either Python, R, or similar,
Working extensively with SQL.
If you also have worked with machine learning, credit modeling, and maybe have programmed some in C#, Java, or similar, it is of course a plus!
So, what’s in it for you?
You will have the opportunity to work hands-on in a fast-paced, exciting, and collaborative scale-up company with ambitious co-workers that also honors the work-life balance. To add an edge to our employee offer we also have a warrant program for everybody working here.
At Froda, you will truly have freedom under responsibility, which means that you will have the ability to impact your own work and tackle a wider set of tasks than in a typical data science role. You have the actual possibilities to impact tech strategy and decisions. We are a passionate team with an open culture, and we truly believe that the best decisions are taken by combining people's knowledge!

If you have any questions or thoughts concerning the role or process, don’t hesitate to send me an email at: john@froda.se.

Title: Data Scientists & Data Engineers
Description:
Nortical improves battery efficiency. We do this by analyzing live battery data in order to compile battery insights that we use to give advice on how to utilize them better in the future.
We are smack in the middle of the creation of a completely new value chain. As the world is electrifying, batteries are becoming the centrepiece of both existing and new business models and products. You will work in the very centre of this change together with a diverse team of like-minded individuals, people truly taking an active role in shaping the future of electrification and how batteries will be used.
We are now looking for a tech-savvy data scientists and data engineers, curious about battery technology and
What You´ll Do
As a start-up team, we all have diverse tasks, but your main focus will be to work on identifying relevant data sets needed for data analytics. Work together with others to integrate and prepare data for analysis. You will also take part in running analytical models, assess the findings and communicate the results to the business team and customers.
Key Qualification
We place great value in intelligence, team sense, and self-drive. But skills are important too. Here follows the skill set that we believe is key for accomplishing your tasks.
High level of fluency in the Python programming language.
Comfortable working with external data sources and CI environments.
Experience with imperfect industry data, e.g noisy, incomplete or badly structured data.
Have experience in writing code within an already established system that has version handling and code review.
Confident working in a start-up environment where we sometimes have to find our own way in unchartered territory.
Self-motivated and meticulous in your problem-solving approach. You should love to learn new things and conduct experiments.
Proficiency in English (Swedish not required).
Bonus Skills
Experience with cloud development (bonus points for Google Cloud). Specifically with deployment and management of models in a production cloud environment.
Experience with data analytics in python, using tools like pandas, TensorFlow, scikit-learn.
Experience with streaming collections of Big Data.
Experience with battery data, or more broadly data that represents a physical system.
Experience with aggregated data.
Experience in writing efficient code to process and analyze large data sets.
Diversity makes a difference
You are welcome to Nortical as the person that you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what your favourite battery chemistry is. The more minds and voices we have, the stronger our business will be, the more we will thrive and develop. It´s in our diversity that we find the secret sauce for our revolutionizing products and creating a better tomorrow.
Does this sound interesting? Please get in touch with Us as soon as possible. We apply a continuous selection process and interviews will be held continuously. So click that apply button now!

Title: BI/Data Arkitekt till vårt Data & Analytics team
Description:
Hos Columbus ges du möjlighet att utveckla din kompetens och arbeta med teknik i framkant. Du arbetar i projektform med olika typer av kunder tillsammans med roliga och kompetenta kollegor!

Som BI arkitekt arbetar du nära vårt Data & Analytics team. Här hittar du allt från BI-konsulter, utvecklare till arkitekter. Du driver lösningsarbetet, bygger smart arkitektur och planerar projektets tekniska inriktning. Samtidigt ger du våra kunder vägledning om plattformar som kan möta nya och föränderliga verksamhetskrav. Vi har en väl utvecklad arbetsmetod och arbetar aktivt för att lyfta fram nya tankesätt och idéer som gäller oavsett om du är arkitekt eller trainee, bäst idé vinner! Internt kommer du även i kontakt med våra konsulter från affärsområdena för Dynamics, M3, and Digital Commerce. På kundsidan arbetar du nära olika kravställare, process- och systemägare.
"En typisk arbetsvecka för mig består av att driva våra kunders tekniska utveckling till att vara moderna och framtidssäkra, och samtidigt förvaltningsbara baserat på förvaltningsorganisationens kompetenser. Jag håller workshops med kundernas tekniska organisation, domänarkitekter och product owners, samt nyckelpersoner på CXO/management nivå för att göra kravinsamling och coacha till förändring. Mitt arbete är även att coacha våra blivande talanger att utmana sig själva och utvecklas, revidera och utforma projektprocesser, hålla mig ajour med uppdateringar beträffande teknik och best practices." - Paul, Lösningsarkitekt
Du arbetar hos kund, på vårt kontor eller på ditt hemmakontor, på det sätt som du trivs bäst med. Du tillhör något av våra kontor i Göteborg, Stockholm eller Malmö och Kim Rasmussen är din konsultchef.
Varför Columbus?
Vi har i över 30 år levererat digitala lösningar till våra kunder och det har vi gjort framgångsrikt. Hur kommer det sig? Jo! På Columbus har vi en omfattande branschkunskap som kombineras med ett stort utbud av digitala lösningar och en rejäl dos kundförståelse. Vi hjälper våra kunder att forma lösningar efter branschspecifika behov så att de kan nå sin fulla digitala potential. Våra affärsområden kan dra nytta av varandra och arbeta med samma kunder i olika skeden av sin digitalisering och därmed erbjuda olika spetskompetenser.

På Data & Analytics får du vara delaktig i ett område som är strategiskt viktigt för Columbus. Vi är en grupp på 50 konsulter i Skandinavien och vi växer!

"Idag jobbar jag på en mer konceptuell nivå än i tidigare roller. Det är inte ovanligt att delta i strategi- och arkitekturmöten på ledningsgruppsnivå med kundverksamheten. På Columbus finns en stor kundflora – vilket ger en bred och intressant inblick i olika typer av projekt och kunder från olika branscher." - Paul, Lösningsarkitekt
Du har med dig
Vi söker dig med erfarenhet av att utforma, driva, motivera, presentera samt realisera lösningsarkitektur för BI-projekt i flera projekt med goda resultat. Du har en förmåga att hantera kundkontakt på olika nivåer, även C-level, och kan utifrån komplexa kravbilder kommunicera detta till en bred publik med varierande bakgrunder. Kommunikation är A och O i den här rollen och därför behöver du behärska både svenska och engelska.
Du känner dig hemma med Datawarehouse Architecture (Kimball / Inmon), ELT/ETL Architecture, BI Governance, Cloud Migration och Cloud Architecture (Azure)
Har kunskap inom Azure Analysis Service, Power BI / Power BI Premium, Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse och Azure SQL.
Tillåts vi få drömma lite och lägger till Version Control (DevOps Git/TFS), Databricks och/eller MDM är du en som vi måste få träffa! Om för all del inte har med dig allt i listan ovan? Sök ändå. Vi vill alltid knyta kontakt med duktiga BI-konsulter!
Ansökan
Hos oss kan du ansöka med din LinkedIn eller CV och du behöver inte fylla i några långa frågeformulär. Rekryteringsprocessen kommer innebära en telefonintervju samt möten med chefer och medarbetare internt. Allt för att du, likväl som vi, ska känna att vi verkligen är en bra match. Har du några frågor om rollen så är du välkommen att kontakta Malin Nyberg.
Mer om Columbus
Columbus är ett värdestyrt bolag med engagerade medarbetare som stöttar varandra i både framgång som motgång. Att ha en god balans mellan arbete och fritid är en självklarhet. Det kan vara allt från hämtning och lämning på förskola till väntan av det där paketet som ska levereras hem ”någon gång mellan 10-19”. Dessutom så är vi riktigt bra på att fira framgångar och det är inte ovanligt med fika, lyxfrukost och AW på kontoret. På Columbus har vi även trevliga förmåner för att stötta våra medarbetare i livets olika stadier.

Spana in vårt Insta-flöde för att få en bild av hur det är att jobba hos oss genom våra kollegor. Klicka på bilden för att komma till Instagram-kontot.
Helt ofiltrerat har vi samlat in omdömen från nuvarande och tidigare kollegor. Klicka nedan för att läsa mer.

Title: Climate Data Analyst Kalmar
Description:
Kalmar keeps global trade moving. Our innovative solutions contribute to every fourth container movement in the world and help transform the future of cargo handling. We believe in collaboration, delivering on our promises and that people make the difference.
Making your next move count

Do you want to make a real impact on the world? We are now looking for a Climate Data Analyst in Kalmar.

In this role you will collect, analyse and present information about potential business opportunities and KPI data within the field of Kalmar climate management to drive strategic and operational decisions. This role is primarily focused on assisting with collecting, analysing and reporting a variety of data to properly drive the sustainability and climate agenda and meet the commitments of being a Science Based target company. Close collaboration with the Cargotec Mission Climate team will also be required. Product use phase data analytics will also be required from time to time.

This position is based in Ljungby and you will report to Kalmar’s Head of Sustainability. This is a hybrid job with the possibility to work from home.
Main tasks and responsibilities

Your main tasks will consist of assessing data requirements and supply master data related to Life Cycle Assessment (LCA), carbon intensity (tCO2e/M€) of portfolio, Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG), Supply chain engagement and performance, Science Based Targets Initiative (SBTi), CRU International data related to steel. You will identify opportunities for improvements with data availability, enterprise data architecture, data processing, reporting, and analytics and audit data quality and identify gaps. You will also deliver results to various stakeholders in a self-service reporting environment and by delivering reports and comparative analytics as needed and coordinate information flow of the above-mentioned topics within the corporation (assure that respective businesses are aware of the inputs).

Other tasks:

Create climate data models and system reports, scenario analysis, etc.
Act as an advocate for data and reporting needs for Sustainability
Support Kalmar and Cargotec to build & maintain CO2 emission reporting systems, integrated with sourcing data and adding CO2 emissions impact in sourcing projects. This includes supporting IM to harmonise and change system platforms to control master data
Build & maintain Eco portfolio reporting systems and emissions tools.

What you’ll need to succeed

Typically university (Bachelor's degree) level or vocational qualification / relevant working experience
Familiar with Kalmar or Cargotec master data and key systems (e.g. GCP, SAP, ERP ́s, CR360)
Preferred experience with management of large amounts and complexity of data, reporting, or analytics
Undertake advanced statistical analysis and use statistical tools and models
Emissions calculation (GHG Protocol) and Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) knowledge or willingness to learn
Solid understanding of best practices of reporting and data visualisation practices.


Our new colleague is someone with strong communication skills, fluent in English, a data-oriented problem solver, able to work independently to complete given assignments.
You have a background in Information Management and a preferred experience with data quality and auditing, project management experience is beneficial.
You will be part of

We believe in our people as it is our people who really make the difference. We always work in close collaboration with our customers, deliver on our promises and never walk away no matter how big the challenge. We succeed because we do it together.

With us, you will have the opportunity to realise your potential and become an important member of our global team.
Interested to join?

For further information please contact Mette Kjems Baerentzen, Head of Sustainability, by email at mette.kjems.baerentzen@kalmarglobal.com

If you are excited about this opportunity, please submit your application by 24.02.2023.
Kalmar is part of Cargotec
Kalmar offers the widest range of cargo handling solutions and services to ports, terminals, distribution centres and to the heavy industry. Kalmar is the industry forerunner in terminal automation and in energy efficient container handling, with one in four container movements around the globe being handled by a Kalmar solution. Through its extensive product portfolio, global service network and ability to enable a seamless integration of different terminal processes, Kalmar improves the efficiency of every move. www.kalmarglobal.com

Kalmar is part of Cargotec. Cargotec's (Nasdaq Helsinki: CGCBV) sales in 2021 totalled approximately EUR 3.3 billion and it employs around 11,500 people.

Title: Technology Graduate Leadership Programme - Sweden
Description:
Technology Graduate Leadership Programme - Sweden
Salary: Competitive
Location: Södertälje & Gothenburg, Sweden
Apply and advance your technology skills to drive digital health and develop life-changing medicines.
About AstraZeneca
Within AstraZeneca IT, we’re at the forefront of discovering and driving digital health and workplace automation to ensure our teams can continue to develop life-changing medicines. And as a member of our Technology Graduate Leadership Programme, you’ll play a huge part in helping drive our innovation.
Here our work has a direct impact on patients – transforming our ability to develop life-changing medicines. We empower the business to perform at its peak and lead a new way of working, combining cutting-edge science with leading digital technology platforms and data. All with a passion to impact lives through data, analytics, AI, machine learning and more.
We truly value our Graduate talent, their experience, knowledge, ideas and who they are. So here, you’ll be empowered to jump in, take the initiative and be part of meaningful project teams to make an impact and deliver real value for our patients and our business.
About the role
As the next wave of technology leaders, you’ll use your skills and influence to deliver technology solutions and help improve the way we operate, serve customers and enable our teams to do their best work. Because here, we truly value your knowledge, experience and ideas. So, you’ll always be encouraged to take the initiative to help drive our technology capabilities and make meaningful impact for our business, and our patients.
We’ve been busy building and developing our technology which is now enabling our transformation to become a digital and data-led enterprise. There’s never been a better time to join us as we bring our digital strategy to life. There’s a huge opportunity to develop, explore and thrive during our next chapter.
Starting in September 2023, the Technology Leadership Graduate Programme begins with three individual eight-month placements. Each placement will provide you with extraordinary insights into our business, and the chance to influence our future direction. If successful during the first 2 years, you will then consolidate your learning and experience in your third year in the programme.
Working alongside diverse, talented peers in an inclusive, supportive environment, the Programme will have you moving through different rotations to hone your skills, develop as a leader, and get where you want to go. Supported by expert managers and mentors to develop life-changing skills and set you up for success.
The pace is fast, and the levels of challenge and responsibility are high, but we always have fun doing it. So, if you’re ready to pursue your passion for technology-led science and challenge the status quo to kickstart your career and make an impact, then we can’t wait to have you on our team.
Essential Requirements
A bachelor’s or master’s level qualification in Technology, Engineering, Science, or a Pure science subject such as Mathematics and Physics, awarded in 2022, or due to be awarded in 2023
The ability to identify and drive innovation and fresh thinking
Passion for Technology
A collaborative approach, and work effectively in a team
A valid passport and willingness to travel, if required
Fluent English language skills
Why join us?
We’re a network of entrepreneurial self-starters who contribute to something far bigger. There’s a diversity of expertise in our Technology group that’s unique to AstraZeneca – it allows us to dive deep into exploring new leading-edge technology. We enable AstraZeneca to perform at its peak by delivering world-class technology and data solutions. Our work unlocks the potential of science.
We optimise and evolutionise AstraZeneca by maximising efficiencies and finding new ways to drive productivity. From automation to data simplification. We’re not afraid to take ownership and run with it.
Empowered with unrivalled freedom. A place to be open and transparent – we speak up, think creatively and share ideas. Our diverse contributions help us to make better decisions. But we have a constant drive to innovate, and an appreciation for high standards. It takes challenging the status quo to add value in our ever-evolving environment. We love it here because put simply, we make a meaningful impact.
Technology at AstraZeneca is a home for purposeful disruptors!
So, what’s next?
Are you already imagining yourself joining our team? Good, because we’d love to hear from you! Click the link to apply and we’ll be in touch as soon as we can.
Applications Open: 24 February 2023
Applications Close: 26 March 2023
Shortly after you submit your application, you will be asked to complete an online assessment (SHL). If shortlisted, you will then be invited to a video interview and finally a full day virtual assessment day.
Our virtual assessment day will be held on 16th May 2023.
You can find out more about the Technology Leadership Programme here: https://careers.astrazeneca.com/technology-leadership-programme

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Do you want to be a part of a new Analytics Operations team and get to work in an inspiring environment? Then you should keep reading!
DevPort are now looking for a Data Analyst to join our clients new Analytics Operations team. The Analytics Operations team should act as a catalyst and take responsibility for analytics value creation in all phases; from early ideation with stakeholders to creating runtime dashboards and data pipelines or guiding superusers to help them create their own dashboards. We also cooperate with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to run AI/ML models in operations. The Analytics Operations team is new and as such you will be part of developing the unit and creating successful use cases.
Our clients new Data, Analytics & AI organization is focused on unleashing the value of data collected from connected customer assets. The team are set out to drive the transformation into a data driven culture, where Data, Analytics & AI/ML are an integral part in their services and internal processes. By spanning across Data Foundation, Data Analytics and Data Science they can provide their stakeholders with actionable insights and take ownership of the whole process from ideation and exploration to analytics operations.

About the role
Drive the data journey by connecting with stakeholders, running workshops, identify opportunities and take it from idea to value.
Develop state-of-the art solutions, dashboards, and insight reports.
Stay at the forefront in the analytics space and share knowledge and experience with colleagues.

Your profile
You have a degree in a relevant field or practical experience from utilizing data to drive change.
You are a creative, entrepreneurial problem-solver with an inquisitive attitude and are not afraid of complex challenges or unconventional approaches.
You routinely use dashboarding as a tool for problem solving, and are experienced in at least one dashboarding solution (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, QuickSight, Grafana).
You confidently and systematically build analysis approaches from scratch, including data extraction, scripting and/or programming in relevant languages and analysis with creation of informative and appealing visualizations.
You are a communicative person that builds and maintains trust with stakeholders and colleagues.
Humorous; because, in the end, working in the team should be fun.

What can we offer you?
You will be part of a highly skilled analytics team that together with our stakeholders creates great value in short- and long-term engagements. In this team you will be able to make a data-driven impact on sustainable transport solutions for our client, their customers and society at large - and have fun while doing it. Your workplace will be based in Lindholmen in Gothenburg.

Application
Apply by following the steps below. If you have any questions regarding the position, send an email to Elin Thulin at elin.thulin@devport.se
I am looking forward to read you application!

About DevPort
DevPort is a technology consulting company in an expansive development phase with headquarter in Gothenburg and offices in Stockholm, Linköping, Helsingborg and Karlskrona. DevPort has its core competence in the automotive industry and employs more than 500 people in three business areas - Digital solutions, production development and product development.
We are proud of our employees and of collaborating with several of the world's leading vehicle manufacturers, companies in the defense industry and other development-intensive industries.
We are characterized by a family culture with entrepreneurship, competence, security and a community that infuses the company's operations and contributes to a pleasant and inspiring workplace.

Title: Konsult inom Data & Analytics
Description:
Vill du fortsätta växa som konsult inom Data & Analytics tillsammans med oss på Business Vision?
Business Vision är en helhetsleverantör inom data och analys med kontor i både Stockholm och Göteborg. Med vår expertis inom Microsofts ledande dataplattform gör vi det lättare att analysera data och identifiera trender, för att våra kunder ska bli mer proaktiva i deras beslutsfattande – Vi gör det enkelt att ta beslut! Vi är stolta över att jobba tillsammans med några av Sveriges ledande varumärken samtidigt som vi har nära partnerskap med Microsoft, Snowflake och Databricks.
Vi på Business Vision är visionärer och strävar efter att efterleva våra värdeord mod, trovärdighet och hjärta i allt vi gör. Med mod är vi nyfikna, kreativa, drivna och strävar ständigt att hålla oss i teknikens framkant. Med trovärdighet fokuserar vi på och utvecklas inom Microsofts molnbaserade dataplattformar för Data Analytics, IoT och AI. Detta fokus ger oss en unik spetskompetens! På Business Vision formar vi våra egna vägar. Vi utvecklas konstant som företag och de anställda deltar i att styra den utvecklingen. Alla tar ansvar för den egna kompetensutvecklingen och vi uppmuntrar till delaktighet i vår erbjudandeutveckling. Med hjärta, ödmjukhet och gemenskap i åtanke stöttar vi varandra att göra vårt allra bästa för våra kunder. Vi ser alla våra anställda, för de är det viktigaste vi har. Därför är tydlighet, jämställdhet, utmaningar och glädje i arbetet något vi konstant strävar efter.
Nu vill vi bli fler i både Stockholm och Göteborg! Därför söker vi dig som:
Har mycket goda kunskaper inom några av följande områden; Data Analytics, Data Engineering, Data Platform, Cloud Platform och/eller Cloud Application Development.
Kan arbeta både självständigt och utefter givna ramverk med merparten av följande tjänster i Azure, kodspråk och verktyg: Function Apps, Logic Apps, Azure Storage (Data Lake v2, Blob storage, etc), Data Factory (inkl. Integration Runtime och Data flow), Key Vault (nyttjande av Managed Identity), DevOps, Azure SQL Database/Managed Instance, Visual Studio Code, SSDT, Javascript, Java, C#, Python, XML, json, sFTP, REST/SOAP
Meriterande kunskap: Byggt lösningar med Runbooks, IoT hub, Event Hubs/grids, Stream Analytics, Azure AD (bl.a. i kombination med MS Graph) och Office Scripts
Utöver ovanstående arbetat med angränsande tekniker från andra leverantörer såsom Snowflake, Matillion, Alteryx, Wherescape samt erfarenhet av Data Vault
Har en relevant akademisk utbildning eller motsvarande kunskaper förvärvade på annat sätt.
Är verksamhetsorienterad och lyhörd, dvs kan förstå kunders behov och mål på riktigt.
Gillar att anta utmaningar och lösa problem.
Har erfarenhet av att leda/koordinera arbete, ansvara för leveranser och kunna vårda och utveckla kundkontakter.
Är flytande i svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift
För att trivas på Business Vision:
Du är nyfiken, driven och vill alltid fortsätta utvecklas
Du ansvarar för och driver din egen kompetensutveckling
Du strävar efter långsiktiga och öppna relationer
Du är ödmjuk, gillar god gemenskap och antar varje uppdrag med hjärta!
På Business Vision gillar vi att träffa varandra och vi ser därför att du är på vårt kontor i Bonnierhuset, Stockholm några dagar i veckan. Tjänsten är på heltid med start omgående om möjlighet finns. Kom och bli en del av oss. Har du några frågar eller funderingar om tjänsten är du varmt välkommen att kontakta Kim Grandell som är Vice VD genom att mejla: kim.grandell@businessvision.se.
PS. Kika in vår Instagram för att få en inblick i hur det är att arbeta hos oss
‍
Varmt välkommen att skicka in din ansökan idag!

Title: Data Analyst, Customer Meeting Points, Customer Domain, Group Digital, Ingka Group
Description:
Who you are

At IKEA, you’re welcome no matter where you come from, what you believe, and what you look like. We don’t even care how you have furnished your home. We’re interested in you simply because you’re you. Our different views, backgrounds, and personalities make us better understand our customers, give us more fun at work and spark more and better ideas. Perhaps your unique take on something could lead to a great idea that creates a better everyday life for the many people.

As a (Senior) Data Analyst, you are an important part in guiding the organisation on how to make best use of one of the world’s possibly largest and most extensive data sets for Web and App. With a growth mindset, you take ownership, enjoy collaborating with various stakeholders, including product owners and engineers, and building a network in a large organisation. You focus on the customer and what the insight from the data means for them.

You also recognize yourself in some of the following:

You’ve experience as a Business Analyst, Data/Web/App Analyst or Data Scientist
You’ve extensive knowledge of data pre-processing techniques, e.g. how to handle missing data
You’ve got a solid knowledge of SQL and the role it plays in data analysis
You’re familiar with cloud computing environments, e.g. Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
You’ve broad knowledge of relevant scripting languages (such as Python) and the role of notebook environments for sharing findings and code with others
You’ve got a good understanding of collaborative software engineering practices (Agile, DevOps, GitOps), in which solutions evolve through the effort of self-organising cross-functional teams
You’re familiar with digital product development principles and the importance of rapid validated learning cycles to optimise performance long-term (preferably in a retail setting)
You do love storytelling and use visualisations of data to explain facts
You’re excited about IKEA’s values and vision of creating a better everyday life for the many people!

The IKEA culture and values are very much a part of our business and day-to-day work life. For you to thrive and grow with IKEA it’s important for us that you share our values! You can read more regarding our values and life at IKEA on our website www.ikea.com.

We are looking for both a Senior Data Analyst and a Data Analyst.

What you'll be doing day to day

Within the Customer Domain of Data & Analytics, you’ll be a part of the Customer Meeting Points area team that focus on Online Data and Tracking pillar both for Web (IKEA online store) and IKEA App. In collaborations mostly with Product and Engineering, you will gather both qualitative and quantitative insights that are needed to impact the roadmap of the products.

This means:
Conduct advanced data exploration and analysis to provide insights that help co-workers and stakeholders make better decisions
Evaluate the potential and usability of raw, unstructured internal and external data sources for use in product analytics and data-driven decision-making in general
Ensure that solutions fulfill and adapt to actual business needs to continuously generate value for Ingka by listening to and guiding fellow team members and co-workers from different functions

Our team within Ikea

We are proud of our vision to create a better everyday life for the many people. We’re working in different locations worldwide to facilitate our digital growth ambition. The office for this role will be Malmö, Sweden, but we act as one global team and work together on global solutions.

We want you to join our diverse team within Data & Analytics consisting of Data Engineers, Data Analysts, Data Scientists, and Data Stewards based across Sweden, the Netherlands and Spain. Our team is filled with people who enjoy good stories and welcome new team members warmly!

We see so many opportunities for what we can accomplish and have the ambition to be a world-class team. At the same time, we believe that our work is not just about solving business problems, but also about learning and having fun together!

WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU

Opportunities to have a global impact with your work on our e-commerce performance on Web & App
Flexible and modern tools: we deploy on GCP and we use lots of open-source tools
Hardware and Operating System of your choice
A team of great colleagues to learn with and from (with world-class experience)
Continuous learning (we aim to spend 20% of our working time on learning)
Flexible and friendly working environment in a truly value-based company!

Questions and support? Let's connect!

Does this sound like your next challenge? IKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global workplace. And as the world’s leader at life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us.

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please reach out to Annette Björkquist-Åhstedt at annette.bjorkquist-ahstedt@ingka.ikea.com

Please apply with your application in English. Note that we can’t process any applications through email. Thank you!

Studies show that members of underrepresented communities don’t apply for jobs unless they’re 100% “qualified”. If this is part of the reason you hesitate to apply, we like you to reconsider and give it a chance. Maybe your profile fits our needs much better than you think. We look forward to receiving your application.

From: “Why Women Don’t Apply for Jobs Unless They’re 100% Qualified” by Tara Sophia Mohr, August 2014”

Title: Head of Analytics
Description:
Do you want to help us unleash the secret to how happy employees create a happy business? We are an innovative, agile, and continuously growing modern tech company on a path to improving the work lives of millions around the world.

We develop workforce management solutions - software that makes scheduling and time reporting more smooth and more flexible for almost a million users worldwide!
We value passion, creativity, quality, and simplicity. You’ll be given the opportunity to make an impact and directly contribute to our success, bring new ideas, and have full ownership of your area.
Our global team, of more than 35 nationalities, have fun together, whether it is during a typical Swedish Fika, a workshop, going for a run with a colleague, or spending time together during the annual company Goal trip, team kickoffs, or after-work socials. We have built a collaborative and friendly atmosphere here at Quinyx and are committed to sharing knowledge and supporting one another!
Are you curious and ready to take the first steps on an awesome journey and make magic happen with us? As a member of Quinyx, you will be part of an inclusive and diverse workplace where everyone is allowed to be themselves and thrive.

About the role
As a part of our growing analytics team, you will take part in developing tomorrow's intelligent workforce management, enabling insights driven decision-making and having a significant impact on strategic initiatives. The mission is to turn our vast amounts of data into actionable insights across the organisation and guide the development of new features and models. The Head of Analytics will lead our analytics team, and work closely with stakeholders and cross-functional teams to leverage data-driven insights to drive business growth. With our international presence, you will be an integral part of a company set out to enable our customers to create a happy business and a happy workforce.
Are you a data and analytics leader with a passion for driving analytics initiatives? Do you have a strong background in data engineering, data analysis, and data science, as well as technical proficiency in programming languages and tools? If so, we want you to lead our analytics team as our Head of Analytics.
What you’ll be doing
Lead a team within data analysis, data engineering, and data science to deliver high-quality insights, analysis, and models that inform key business decisions
Develop and drive the vision, strategy, and execution of the analytics function within the organisation
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities for data-driven innovation and optimization
Ensure the right technical capabilities, tools, and systems are in place to support the analytics efforts
Build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders to ensure alignment on analytics priorities and objectives
Mentor and develop team members to ensure they have the skills and knowledge needed to grow and deliver high-quality work
Stay ahead of industry trends and best practices
What you’ll bring to the team
MSc degree in Engineering, Physics, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, or equivalent quantitative field.
4+ years of experience managing data & analytics teams
Strong leadership skills and a track record of leading by example
Strong skill set and profound background in the data & analytics field spanning from data engineering, analysis to science.
Technical proficiency in programming languages and tools such as Python, Spark, SQL, R, and data visualisation tools.
Strategic mindset with great business acumen
Ability to build and maintain strong relationships with stakeholders at all levels of the organisation
Strong communication skills
Experience working within the SaaS space
What’s in it for you?
We promote and encourage a healthy lifestyle with flexible work hours and the latest tools, enhanced vacation allowance, wellness, home office, professional development contributions, virtual yoga classes, and last but not least, you will have the chance to participate in our well-known yearly ping-pong tournament!

Want to join Quinyx?
At Quinyx, we provide equal employment opportunities and strive for an inclusive, diverse, value-driven culture. All applications will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, disability, or veteran status.
Happy Workforce, Happy Business!

Title: Data Steward, Customer Domain, Malmö/Madrid, Group Digital, INGKA Group
Description:
Who you are

IKEA is taking huge steps in its digital transformation and our Data Stewards are working in cross-functional teams to transform IKEA into a more data-driven company by ensuring our analytics is built on world-class data!

You like problem-solving and supporting others with data and you are not afraid to innovate to find a better way to do things. And you like working with people to find lasting solutions. All this while you solve real problems for IKEA customers and co-workers.

You will join a diverse team within Data & Analytics consisting of data analysts, data scientists, data engineers, data stewards, and machine learning engineers based across Sweden, the Netherlands, and Spain.

You recognize yourself in some of the following:
A curious world-class problem solver who wants to keep learning!
Consider data to be the starting point for solving (almost) any business problem
Ability to define and implement logic (e.g., via SQL and regular expressions) to do data validation and build data quality metrics
Knowledge of modern tools and principles for Data Governance at scale in an industry setting
Conceptual knowledge of data models (e.g. hierarchical, relational) and ability to translate them into practical improvements
Extensive knowledge of common issues related to data quality, and how to improve them
Good knowledge of data ethics-related challenges in society and how they impact operations in IKEA (collection, storage, and usage)
Extensive understanding of data privacy regulatory frameworks, and how to actively work with compliance at IKEA in different markets
Passionate about the possibilities of Data & Analytics and the value they can generate for the business

This is our wish list! If you don’t recognize yourself in all these points, you might still be an excellent candidate for the role. We like to think long-term and invest in people’s development together with us.

What you'll be doing day to day

You’ll lead the transformation of IKEA into a more data-driven company by ensuring that we have the right data, in the right place and at the right time.

For example, we are working to solve problems like:
How can we be quicker in spotting issues in data quality?
How can we motivate the people around us to take care of their data, and be just as excited as us about the opportunities that the data present?
How can we make it easier to use the data we have?
How can we ensure that the right people have access to the right data at the right time?
How can we maximize learning from our data, and at the same time ensure that we continue to have Data Ethics as our main priority?

Our team within Ikea

You will work in Data & Analytics together with data analysts, data scientists, data engineers, data stewards, and machine learning engineers. Together you will be joining cross-functional teams consisting of colleagues from Technology, Product, and Design in the domain. All of you together will be creating the best solutions to serve our customers with a frictionless buying journey across all touchpoints.

WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU

Opportunities to have a global impact on your work
Flexible and modern tools: we deploy on Google Cloud Platform and we use a lot of open source tools across the board
Hardware and Operating System of your choice
A team of great colleagues to learn with and from (with world-class experience across all aspects of Data & Analytics)
Continuous learning (we aim to spend 20% of our working time on learning)
Flexible and friendly working environment in a truly value-based company

Questions and support? Let's connect!

Does this sound like your next challenge? IKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global workplace. And as the world’s leader in life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us.

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please reach out to Annette Björkquist-Åhstedt at annette.bjorkquist-ahstedt@ingka.ikea.com. Please apply with your application in English. Note that we can’t process any applications through email. Thank you!

During The Holidays

We just want to let you know that the process may take a little longer than normal during the Christmas holidays, but we will be up and running again at full capacity as of January 10th.

Happy Holidays!

Title: Principal Data & Analytics Architect
Description:
What makes us Qlik
Qlik helps enterprises around the world move faster, work smarter, and lead the way forward with an end-to-end solution for getting value out of data. A Gartner Magic Quadrant Leader for 12 years in a row! Our platform is the only one on the market that allows for open-ended, curiosity-driven exploration, giving everyone – at any skill level – the ability to make real discoveries that lead to real outcomes and transformative changes. We are a Values-Driven organization operating in over 100 countries with 38,000 customers around the world. If you think we are interesting, please read on – we may be looking for you!

Principal Data & Analytics Architect
The Principal Data & Analytics Architect’s main responsibility will be to, in conjunction with architecture leadership, identify, analyze and support the enterprise’s business drivers through enablement of data and/or information strategies.

The Senior architect will lead and support the development and evolution of Qlik’s data policies and approaches with a goal of enabling data analytics and data science. A data governance program and its standards will be pragmatically supported to derive optimum business value while ensuring data security and privacy requirements are fully met.

The successful candidate will possess excellent oral and written communication skills and extensive technology acumen which they use to drives results, and lead through influence. They must be able to build strong relationships by working collaboratively with all levels of the organization.

Responsibilities include:

Working across the organization to maintain a data strategy that adheres to the target architecture and roadmap which maximizes the value of information assets via their creation, access, and use.
Working with delivery and product teams to ensure that system designs comply with the target state architecture and help in the selection of product and / or solutions to deliver business outcomes.
Enabling desired business outcomes through analytics, governance, and enterprise information policy administration.
Ensuring that the enterprise architecture is used as a lens and filter to identify, prioritize and execute the data and analytic initiatives with clear line of sight to enterprise strategies and business outcomes.
Supporting the data and information governance model across all business units.
Maintaining information reference architecture, standards, and design patterns.
Building and maintaining data flow diagrams, enterprise and solution data models, and data lineage diagrams.
Reviewing and recommending data quality metrics and translate data quality issues into improvements to data ingestion and / or management.

Qualifications include:
Bachelor's degree in IT, Engineering, Computer Science, or equivalent experience.
Qlik Sense Administrator certification (preferred).
QlikView Administrator certification (preferred).
Minimum of 10 years of experience in technology, with at least 5 years in information system design and architecture.
Experience in designing and implementing big data solutions using cloud native solutions with experience in event-based architecture and data lineage tools.
Experience in designing solutions that leverage machine learning models with real-time decision engines that enable customer centric experiences.
Hands-on experience with implementing data and analytics management programs and data governance practices.
Knowledge of, and experience in, implementing data security, data privacy and data residency policies.
Understanding of common information architecture frameworks and information models.
Understanding of data science concepts, as well as MDM (Master Data Management), CDP (Customer Data Platform), BI (Business Intelligence), DWH (Data Warehouse) design and implementation techniques.
Exposure to and experience with AI/ML.
Experience with distributed management and analytics in cloud and hybrid environments.
An understanding of a variety of data access and analytics approaches including microservices and event-based architectures.
Experience with data streaming technologies.
Ability to assess rapidly changing technologies and apply them to business needs.
Business acumen and the ability to communicate to project managers, business domain stakeholders and technical staff alike.
Must have the ability to resolve issues, mitigate roadblocks, and align teams consistently and collaboratively.
Experience working with AWS, Snowflake, and modern data technologies across ingestion, transformation, and extraction/consumption.

Location

This position can be located in either US or Canada or Sweden.

About Qlik
Qlik Company Page – Who we are!
Our Values at Qlik: Challenge, Take Responsibility, Move Fast, Take Responsibility, Be Open and Straightforward
Competitive Benefits package

Title: Team Manager till Insights & Data
Description:
Insights & Data är på en stark tillväxtresa och söker nu ytterligare en teamchef för att bidra till våra framgångar. Med en ny Hybrid & Flexible Work Policy arbetar vi tillsammans för att växa regionen med medarbetare i både Malmö och Helsingborg.
Om oss:
Insights & Data är marknadsledande inom Data, AI och Analytics och våra tjänster inkluderar konsultverksamhet inom bl.a. Analytics, Data Governance, Data Engineering, Data Science, AI & Machine Learning. Vi arbetar med såväl stora globala som mindre lokala kunder vilket ger våra konsulter en varierad arbetsdag och möjlighet till att ständigt utvecklas och lära nytt.
Insights & Data South har kontor i Malmö och i Helsingborg och består idag av sex konsultteam med närmare 100 medarbetare samt en lokal säljorganisation och ledningsgrupp. Vi samarbetar nära med våra kollegor på den svenska såväl som globala marknaden vilket ger oss kompetens och kapacitet att verkligen göra skillnad för våra kunder. Som teamchef i regionen kan du tillhöra antingen kontoret i Malmö eller i Helsingborg, men förväntas röra dig mellan kontoren vid behov. Du har även möjlighet att arbeta hemifrån som en del av vår Hybrid & Flexible Work Policy.
Om rollen:
Våra medarbetare är det viktigaste vi har och ett värderingsstyrt och empatisk ledarskap är viktigt för oss inom Insights & Data South. Då våra medarbetare arbetar hos kund, från våra lokala kontor såväl som hemifrån, ställer detta skifte stora krav på ett empatiskt, lyhört och närvarande ledarskap.
Vi arbetar ständigt med att vidareutveckla vår affär, vår personal och vårt erbjudande. Vi är resultatdrivna och arbetar tillsammans för att uppnå våra mål. Detta samtidigt som vi leder med hjärtat och ser till att våra medarbetare trivs, utvecklas och har roligt tillsammans. Vår lokala FUN committee hjälper oss att skapa trevliga stunder och vi har en tradition med Team Thursday då vi uppmanar våra konsulter att vara på kontoret, träffa sina kollegor och fika tillsammans.
Inclusion & Diversity är våra ledord och styrka - vår region består idag av medarbetare från hela världen med olika bakgrunder och erfarenheter såväl som olika åldrar, kön, sexualitet och religioner. För att lyckas i rollen och trivas väl i regionen tror vi att du har tidigare erfarenhet av att leda människor från olika kulturer och bakgrunder samt att du behärskar engelska i tal och skrift.
Vi tror att du som söker är initiativtagande och gillar att leda, driva och utveckla medarbetare såväl som oss som företag. Du uppskattar ett kreativt arbetsklimat med internationella kontaktytor. Som person är du självgående, strukturerad, driven, engagerad och lösningsorienterad.
I rollen ingår:
Formellt personalansvar för team på mellan 15-25 personer
Rekrytering till ditt team
Hjälpa och coacha konsulterna i sin karriär- och kompetensutveckling
Verksamhetsutveckling och ledningsarbete
Samarbete med övriga teamchefer, säljorganisation, leveransansvariga och stödfunktioner för att nå budget, finansiella resultat och mätetal inom medarbetarnöjdhet
Du sitter i regionens ledningsgrupp och blir en viktig del i det operativa ledningsarbetet och affärsplaneringen. Du rapporterar till vår regionchef / Head of South; Malin Unger.
Rollen innebär 50% arbete som Team Manager och 50% arbete i konsultuppdrag i linje med din kompetens
Vi söker dig med:
Tidigare erfarenhet inom ledarskap, gärna från konsultverksamhet
Genuint intresse för människor där du brinner för att utveckla andra såväl som dig själv
Relevant högskoleexamen eller motsvarande erfarenhet
... och gärna erfarenhet av / att du behärskar:
Bakgrund inom något av våra fokusområden (Data, analytics & AI)
Svenska i tal och skrift
Ansökan
Urval sker löpande, men skicka in din ansökan redan idag, och senast den 2022-02-28
Tillsättning sker snarast.
Har du frågor eller funderingar kontakta gärna Anna Karlsson, Insights & Data Recruitment - anna.karlsson@capgemini.com
Vi ser fram emot att ta emot din ansökan!

Title: Lead Researcher
Description:
Want to have a flexible job where you can work from home? Are you proud of your work and strive to become better and have the oppurtunity to advance your career?
About Brightvision
Brightvision has been a renowned Scandinavian tech marketing/lead generation agency for almost twenty years, working for the largest suppliers of IT solutions (such as IBM, Oracle and Microsoft). Our headquarter is in Gothenburg, Sweden, but as an remote company we have colleauges working all over the world. We are now looking to strenghten the Data & Analytics team with a Lead Researcher as we are growing rapidly. At Brightvision we have a strong belief in the Scandinavian culture, where teamwork is very important for us and even if you work remote you will always feel like you are part of a team of supportive colleagues.
Our business
Our focus is on the first part of the sales process, where we help large IT companies to qualify leads from demand generation activity and to generate new pipeline for our clients sales force. We are educated in our clients technical solutions, we contact decision makers and talk to them about their current solutions and challenges within IT. If their is an interest we book a meeting and after that hand over the dialogue to our client to take over. You will be a part of the begining in this process helping to amongst other enrich the leads.
The position
As a lead researcher you will be a part of the the Data & Analytics team working closely with project managers covering multiple countries, helping the team to enrich leads and improving the quality of data. Working with various tools (You will have the opportunity to add on more tools if needed) and databases to enrich leads for our projects.
What we offer
Brightvision is a "People First" value based company that always strives to keep our employees happy and motivated, by a number of initiatives. A few things we do have in order to do this:
Offer internal coaching and education, improving your professioal skills
For persons who are able and intersted to have a career path towards management positions, we do have a clear development track a Project Manager/Team Leader.
Bi-weekly One on One with your Team Manager
Yearly bonus program
Working with well know industry leading brands
Who are you?
A persistent, highly focused, detail oriented and result-driven person.
Previous experience as a lead researcher and/or data researcher.
Speak and write English in a professional way
Coachable and willing to learn
Interested to work in a fast paced environment where we strive to offer excellent services to our clients, every day
You are available to start part-time as freelancer (invoicing every month).


If you feel that you are the perfest match for this role, please send us your application as soon as possible, but no later than the 15/1 2023
Welcome with your application!

Title: Trainee
Description:
Req ID:406979
Leading societies to a low carbon future, Alstom develops and markets mobility solutions that provide the sustainable foundations for the future of transportation. Our product portfolio ranges from high-speed trains, metros, monorail, and trams to integrated systems, customised services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility solutions. Joining us means joining a caring, responsible, and innovative company where more than 70,000 people lead the way to greener and smarter mobility, worldwide

Support Alstom in growing; finding our new and future colleagues to create and deliver better mobility in Sweden.
Alstom Sweden look for a thesis student/internship student with aspiration to be part of the Alstom family, to start their journey with us.

If you’re looking for a company with a strong purpose and the ambition to play a role in climate change by leading the way to greener and smarter mobility, if you are ambitious and would like to embark on a challenging, global journey, and if you have a certain sense of entrepreneurship: come and leave your mark on the world, with us! We are Agile, Inclusive and Responsible: our AIR values help define who we are—and who we want to be.

If you are communicative, analytical, responsible, and most of all have a willingness to learn, then you can start building on your professional foundation at ALSTOM. We welcome you to send your application to us and we will try to match your aspirations with our internal need and keep an eye on our career page for specific summer work opportunities with us.

Requirements:

Degree/education field:
Student from technical universities on Maters level, with specialisations that fit Alstom business. For this position it is beneficial to have an interest in ecodesign or sustainability as well as knowledge in engineering.

Technical competencies:
Computer literacy
Good knowledge of Microsoft Office
Data entry
Data analytics
Sustainability
Engineering

Other skills:
Agility
Flexibility
High level of adaptability
Very good communication skills
English writing and speaking

Alstom is the leading company in the mobility sector, solving the most interesting challenges for tomorrow’s mobility. That’s why we value inquisitive and innovative people who are passionate about working together to reinvent mobility, making it smarter and more sustainable. Day after day, we are building an agile, inclusive and responsible culture, where a diverse group of people are offered opportunities to learn, grow and advance in their careers, with options across functions and geographic locations. Are you ready to join a truly international community of great people on a challenging journey with a tangible impact and purpose?

Equal opportunity statement:
Alstom is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive working environment where all our employees are encouraged to reach their full potential, and individual differences are valued and respected. All qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by local law.


Job Segment: Data Entry, Trainee, Intern, Administrative, Entry Level
