Title: Senior Data Engineer, Customer Support and Returns, Malmö
Description:
Who you are

Hej!

My name is Stefan Esping and I’m leading the Data & Analytics capabilities in the Customer Support sub-domain. For our Digital hub in Malmö, we are looking for a senior data engineer to help improve the customer experience when needing support from IKEA. We have a huge amount of data that we want to use to improve our IT tools services and we need your help to achieve this. Come join us!

IKEA is taking huge steps in its digital transformation and our Data Engineers are working in cross-functional teams to transform IKEA into a more data driven company by building and supporting state-of-the-art data products.
We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer with minimum 5 years of professional experience as a (Junior) Data Engineer or Software Engineer, to join our diverse and growing team within Data & Analytics and we would love to talk with you if you recognize yourself in some of the following:

Strong knowledge of advanced data structures, distributed computing, and cloud-based services, in particular Google Cloud Platform
Strong knowledge of new and emerging tools for extracting, ingesting, and processing of large datasets (Dataflow, Apache Spark, Beam, Kafka, or equivalent)
Extensive knowledge of programming languages (e.g. Java, Go, Python, or Scala), including concepts from functional and object-oriented programming paradigms
Extensive knowledge of SQL for data processing and analysis, as well as tools such as DBT or Dataform
Broad knowledge of digital product development principles and the importance of rapid validated learning cycles to optimise performance long term
Broad knowledge of collaborative software engineering practices (Agile, DevOps), in which solutions evolve through the effort of self-organising cross-functional teams
A team player who takes ownership, builds cross-functional relationships with senior peers, and loves sharing knowledge with more junior team members
A curious world class problem solver who wants to keep learning!

This is our wish list! If you don’t recognize yourself in all these points, you might still be an excellent candidate for the role. We like to think long-term and invest in people’s development together with us.

The IKEA culture and values are very much a part of our business and day to day work life. For you to thrive and grow with IKEA it’s important for us that you share our values! You can read more regarding our values and life at IKEA on our website www.ikea.com.

What you'll be doing day to day

This Senior Data Engineer role will be driving the development of data products for delivering digital solutions that will improve the IKEA customers experience. The capability area handles most of the solutions used by our customer support centres globally such as communication platform, knowledge management, intelligence and reporting, staff planning, case management, returns management and also self-service solutions for things like appointment/event booking and order management. Most of these solutions have both a customer and co-worker facing part.

The home office for this role will be Malmö but we act as one global team and work together on global solutions. We see so many opportunities for what we can accomplish and have the ambition to be a world class team. At the same time, we believe that our work is not just about solving business problems, but also about learning and having fun together.

Our team within Ikea

You will work together with Data Analysts, Data Scientists, Data Engineers, Machine Learning Engineers and Data Architects. Together you will be joining cross-functional teams consisting of colleagues from Technology, Product, Design, that designs, implements and deploys products that help to solve these kinds of problems. Your job will a mix of understanding business needs, designing data solutions – and of course writing code.

We can offer you:

Work on some very interesting problems as described above, and you are encouraged to spot new opportunities or to collaborate with Data & Analytics colleagues in other teams.
Opportunities to have global impact with your work.
Flexible and modern tools: we deploy on Google Cloud Platform and we use a lot of open source tools across the board.
Hardware and OS of your choice.
A team of great colleagues to learn with and from (with world-class experience across all aspects of Data & Analytics).
Continuous learning (we aim to spend 20% of our working time on learning).
Flexible and friendly working environment.

Questions and support? Let's connect!

Does this sound like your next challenge? IKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global workplace. And as the world’s leader at life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us.

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please reach out to Olivia at olivia.de.peyronnet@ingka.com. Please apply in English and we can’t process any applications through email. Thank you!

Title: System Architect - Data & Analytics
Description:
Vill du driva modernisering, förflyttning och konsolidering i en komplex IT-miljö? Då kan vi erbjuda dig ett intressant arbete med goda utvecklingsmöjligheter i en stimulerande miljö då vi nu satsar på att förflytta hela vår affär in i framtiden.
Ditt uppdrag och ansvar som System Architect inom Data & Analytics är att utveckla och modernisera vårt IT-landskap inom ditt område. IT arbetar efter en agil filosofi där du som medarbetare och med dina kollegor i teamet får ett stort mandat i kraft av er kompetens.
Det här gör du som System Architect inom Data & Analytics
Som System Architect ansvarar du för att upprätthålla och vidareutveckla arkitekturen för Folksamgruppen inom ditt område. Du är en viktig del i arbetet med att sätta målbilder som överensstämmer med vår långsiktiga, strategiska vision samt se till att lösningarna blir kostnadseffektiva, moderna och uppfyller regulatoriska krav. Det är självklart att du känner ett stort engagemang för våra strategiska satsningar och tar ett stort ansvar för att driva arbetet framåt i nära samverkan med utvecklingsteamen, tågen samt övriga arkitekter hos oss. I rollen ingår även att hålla sig uppdaterad med trender och agera kunskapssökande inom nya innovationer och den tekniska utvecklingen inom området.
Ditt övergripande uppdrag är att utforma, dokumentera, visualisera och kommunicera förmågor inom Data & Analytics. Folksam har en lång IT-historia och har naturligtvis existerande plattformar som ska vidareutvecklas, omformas och i många fall avvecklas. En viktig del av ditt arbete kommer därför att vara att definiera transitionsarkitekturer för hur vi når målbilderna över tid och motverkar att vi duplicerar förmågor inom ditt område men också belysa om det sker på andra områden.
Specifikt för uppdraget gäller att du ska agera som fokalpunkt för teknik-, utvecklings- och plattformsfrågor inom ditt område. Du ska ha kunskap och erfarenhet både om specifika tekniker och plattformar men också om Folksams arkitekturella och agila arbetssätt. Det innefattar både kunskap om teknik och plattformsimplementation, de tekniker och standards som tjänsterna använder sig av samt kunskap om samverkande leverantörer och avtal för att leverera dessa.
Du samverkar tätt med andra arkitekter, utvecklare och affärsintressenter i operativa, taktiska och strategiska frågeställningar kring landskapet samt bär ”teknikfanan” i strategisk/taktisk dialog med leverantörer. Du ansvarar för att rekommendera vägval baserat på ekonomi, kompetens, teknikval och implementationssätt samt lämpliga och effektiva leveransmodeller.
Du ansvarar för de teknikplattformar som stöttar Folksamgruppens behov inom data och analys, såsom Business Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Warehousing och Masterdata men också underliggande infrastruktur i molnet där vi arbetar med infrastruktur som kod. Arkitektur, teknik och modern analysplattform ska stötta förflyttning mot effektivare informationsförsörjning som leder till ett mer datadrivet bolag samt snabbare insikter.
Är du den vi söker?
Vi söker dig som har flerårig erfarenhet av arkitekturarbete inom data & analytics i komplexa organisationer. Vi jobbar med Microsoft Azure och det är därför särskilt önskvärt om du har erfarenhet av det området, och helst har arbetat inom Data & Analytics i Azure. Du har tidigare erfarenhet inom data science, data engineering, ETL-utveckling, analys och rapportering och agila arbetssätt. Har du dessutom erfarenhet som chef eller ledare ser vi det som meriterande.
Som person ser vi att du är kreativ, resultatinriktad och övertygad om att det alltid finns lösningar på komplexa problem. Du är ansvarstagande och har hög förmåga att driva frågor själv. Du involverar och vägleder andra och samarbetar gärna tvärfunktionellt. Vidare skapar du förtroende genom bemötande och kunskap och ser ständigt lärande som en självklarhet.
Vill du vara med och påverka Folksams förflyttning till molnet och driva vår digitaliseringsresa framåt i ett företag med stort hjärta där IT är högt på agendan så har du chansen nu. Vi lovar dig att det kommer bli både lärorikt och spännande!
Utvecklas tillsammans med oss
Folksam är ett kundägt företag med stort fokus på hållbarhetsfrågor. Vi har många roliga, utvecklande jobb och bra förmåner. Vi tror på ett hållbart arbetsliv och hos oss har du goda chanser till en spännande karriär. Vi erbjuder flexibilitet att varva arbete på kontoret och hemifrån utifrån verksamhetens behov. Våra trevliga kontor runt om i landet ger mötesplatser för samarbete, lärande och en gemensam kultur – tillsammans skapar vi engagemang och kraft framåt! På folksam.se/jobb-och-karriar kan du läsa mer och se filmer om hur det är att jobba på Folksam.
Så söker du jobbet
Välkommen med din ansökan så fort som möjligt men senast 20 februari 2023.
För mer information om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande chef Jacob Karmehag, 072-468 71 83 eller Henrik Nose 070-831 52 82.
Fackliga representanter: Forena Morgan Svensson, 073-423 59 12, Akademikerföreningen Per Hansson 070-831 60 67 och Handels Mikael Carlsson 070-831 51 32.
Folksamgruppen erbjuder försäkringar och långsiktigt sparande som skapar trygghet i livets alla skeden. Vi är cirka 4 000 medarbetare och vår vision är att våra kunder ska känna sig trygga i en hållbar värld. Vi engagerar oss i det våra kunder bryr sig om och är måna om att de är rätt försäkrade.

Title: Enterprise Architect-Shared Data & Information Domains|Inter IKEA Technology Services AB
Description:
About the role
Are you a passionate IT Architect curious about data and technology, and looking to play a key role in shaping the future of a data and information landscape for an ethical global business?
Well, at IKEA we're looking for someone just like you to support the domain of Data and Information across all value streams in IKEA from a Shared Data & Technology angle. We're on a journey to create a robust information architecture as a key element of our target technology landscape, enabling our business movements at speed and scale. We are seeking a talent IT Architect to support this journey and the process of identifying new technologies that will allow and enable us to meet more of the many people.
With the introduction of an enterprise-wide Data & Analytics (D&A) platform, democratizing data throughout Inter IKEA, the business usage of data is recognised to grow rapidly. Consequently, data governance and data sharing processes and tools/platforms that will help end users in consuming the right, on-time data are becoming increasingly important.
You will bring your energy, drive, data and technical expertise into enablement and support of the broad range of data and information topics. In this domain, a wide variety of problem statements, often stretching over the virtual boundaries of Data & Analytics (D&A), Data Integration & Distribution (DD&I) and Information Management (IM), are addressed. Typical assignments range from supporting tool assessment through architecture to in-depth discussions and recommendations around target architectures and roadmaps. You work closely with the D&I EA lead, together you form the conscience of Data & Information domain.
More specific capabilities may include;
Supporting the framing of all initiatives with a robust Data & Information architecture direction and fit with shared responsibility for our roadmap.
Responsible for up-to-date architecture artefacts and data architecture patterns. Partnering with project teams to design, create and re-use the same.
Developing a network strengthening the foundational of a consistent data architecture across applications, integrations, and analytics.
Support the D&I lead to anchor our IKEA canonical data model. Together partner with Data & Analytics, as well as Integration teams to implement a decoupled data architecture, and a set of business APIs, independent of transactional systems.
You will report to our Architecture Manager in Shared Data & Technology and work closely with the Data & Information Architecture Lead to lead towards uniformity and commonality, contributing to the D&I architecture framework and delivering on the needs of IKEA.
About you
As an Enterprise Architect, you'll inspire and mobilise others towards set objectives. You should have a solid understanding of information and business technologies, specifically Enterprise Architecture concepts, methodologies and frameworks. We're looking for passionate, curious and adaptable people who embrace change and want to make a difference.
Hands-on experience implementing a Data and Information architecture framework in a global business with a changing application landscape would be very interesting for this role. We're looking for a visionary, pragmatic architect with strong willpower and the ability to build trust between the architecture community and stakeholders. If you share our values and are excited about the opportunity to make a real impact, apply now. Join us on a journey to transform our digital capabilities at IKEA Shared Data & Technology.
Leadership at IKEA is simple, clear and humble. We’re not fans of bureaucracy and complicated hierarchy. We believe that what you value is more important than what your CV says. Come see things a little differently with us.

More Information

A few more details for you
This is a full time role (40 hours per week) reporting to the Architecture Manager. We would welcome a covering letter to support your application, so we can understand your why! Tell us, as part of your application, why you think you would be a good fit for this role. February 1st 2023 is the closing date to apply for this role.
This role can be based in Malmö, Sweden or Delft, Netherlands, The role is full time and hybrid. At IKEA we see the power of being physically together for collaboration, dialogues and conversations. We believe in the power of human interactions; the informal chats, the energy, belonging and creativity generated by people being in the same place. Our approach is that we spend time in the IKEA workplace with flexibility to work from home.
About us
Inter IKEA Group brings together three core businesses: Franchise, Range and Supply. Together we work constantly to improve the IKEA home furnishing offer and make it more accessible for the many people.
We started establishing a new IKEA Shared Data & Technology organisation as part of developing our digital capabilities. This organisation will be built up together with existing co-workers, recruitments and establishing and developing partnerships over the coming years. It is now an opportunity to join us and be part of and leading this development journey. Our data & technology capabilities that are common across Inter IKEA group will be kept together and organised in the IKEA Shared data & technology organisation. The organisation will be based mainly in southern part of Sweden and in Delft, Netherlands.
Together, we create a workplace where everyone feels free to be themselves – to experiment, try new ways, and dare to ask, “What if…?” We believe in everyday personal growth and offer the opportunity to develop your career globally.

Title: Data Scientist Manager
Description:
We believe that our future success will be based on our ability to leverage the large amounts of data generated on our platform every day. We need the ability to gain fast insights from usage of our services to enable short cycles of product refinement and be able to develop new data-driven services based on all of our data.
During 2020 we began migrating our backend services to the Google Cloud Platform (GCP) with the ambition of being one of the few banks with cloud-based services in a highly regulated industry. During 2021 we started to build our next generation data & analytics environment on top of that and also on GCP.
This year we will focus more on personalisation and develop the capabilities we need to be able to use data-driven services to personalise the customer experience and contribute to other strategic goals.
About the role
As a Data Scientist Manager your focus will be to develop, implement and maintain different types of data-driven services together with other Data scientists and development teams, as well as lead Data scientists and Data analysts.
This role is part of Data & Insights at Nordnet, consisting of data engineering, business intelligence and data science competence responsible for the new environment, spanning from data pipelines to dashboards to data-driven services as well as data analysts supporting the organisation with insights in the daily work. The Data scientists and Data analysts are integrated in other development teams to ensure that we understand the customer needs and develop the best data-driven services and insights.
As Data Science Manager you are responsible for the outcome of your teams, and you use coaching, facilitation and your practical experience to help your teams grow, succeed and continuously deliver value. You are also responsible for hiring, staffing and onboarding.
About you
You are passionate about data, leadership and want to contribute with your experience and knowledge when we take our next steps in developing data-services and supporting the organisation with insights.
As a Data Scientist Manager we believe that this is you
Experience from Machine Learning frameworks and developing end-to-end projects in production.
Experience from working in GCP
Strong communication skills and have the ability to engage both technical and non-technical stakeholders in our vision
An empathic leader, willing to share your knowledge and mentoring and coaching others.
Experience of driving change in an organisation
Good understanding of data engineering practices and data modelling
Bank and Finance experience
Hold a BA degree or equivalent in engineering, computational or technical subject.
What we offer
Nordnet started from a passionate belief that changing the hierarchical financial world was possible. We became part of redefining the industry when we gave the customers power over their own savings. You will become part of a journey that has only yet started towards the vision of making our customers the best investors they can be. To be leading in IT is pivotal for that journey and you will work with colleagues who have a great passion for that goal.
We are 800 employees in Stockholm, Oslo, Helsinki and Copenhagen. We cooperate, exchange ideas and use our core competencies in order to continuously improve the way we meet our customers. Open communication, creativity and engagement are important parts of our everyday life at the office.
Visit us on www.nordnetab.com,www.nordnet.se,
www.nordnet.no, www.nordnet.dk_ and _www.nordnet.fi.
Application
We will start interviewing immediately. Please note that we do only accept applications through our recruitment system, hence no email applications will be considered.
If you have questions, please contact Talent Acqusition Partner Alva Hellberg at alva.hellberg@nordnet.se
We want to inform you that Nordnet conducts credit and background checks on the final candidate.
We look forward to receiving your application!
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Data Engineer - Office/Remote
Description:
Build a better world (together with us)!
We know, those are big words. But it's not every company that is in a position to change how an entire industry works and to solve a massive climate challenge at the same time.

We are BIMobject, the world's leading marketplace for connecting architects and manufacturers. We’re a fast-growing SaaS company providing next-generation solutions for the construction industry to power digital design.

We cherish the spirit of innovation with a playful working environment where we experiment, learn, and help each other to solve problems while working towards creating a better future for our planet.

Who are you?
We are looking for a highly motivated Data Engineer with a passion for data and a strong understanding of data engineering principles. You have a track record of successfully designing and implementing data pipelines, and are eager to both explore your own ideas and utilise proven methodologies. You like working from the office, or from your home - or both!

More about your experience
Comfortable in an international team with English as your daily language
Experienced in building data workflows and implementing data warehousing solutions (ex. GBQ)
Experience with
SQL
Cloud platforms such as Google Cloud Platform and Microsoft Azure
Containerization ex. Kubernetes
Airflow, dbt and other commonly used technologies


Extra awesome
Interest in ML/AI
Data analytics skills

As our new Data Engineer, you will…
Join our small and performant Data team and work with experienced professionals to help us leverage the power of data
Manage our data pipeline and build and maintain the data platform, a great opportunity to own and drive the complete data solution
Improve data quality, integrity and consistency through testing, tooling and evaluating performance continuously
Stay up-to-date with the latest trends and best practices in data engineering

What do we do?
BIMobject.com is a platform where we connect manufacturers of building materials with architects and engineers so they can work on building projects together. BIM enables more efficient processes in the project pipeline leading to less costs, less waste and fewer delays. Getting access to all the BIM content on our site helps the construction industry to build right from the start while giving support in finding environmentally sound products.

What we offer our employees
BIMobject is a company founded in 2011 and headquartered in Malmö, Sweden, with colleagues all over the world: Malmö, Budapest, Madrid, Gliwice, Milan, Munich and on. We value our cultural diversity and the many perspectives our employees bring. For those interested, we offer the opportunity to live and work abroad. However, as we speak 16+ languages at the Malmö HQ, you don't have to go far to get the international vibe.

The start-up mentality is an important part of us, meaning that we never want to stop experimenting and learning and we love to see our people grow. We prioritise continuous personal development by investing in our engaged employees. Finally and maybe most importantly, we want all our employees to have the possibility to shape their work and have their say in how we drive our company forward.

We are proud to foster a workplace free from discrimination. We strongly believe that diversity of experience, perspectives, and background will lead to a better environment for our employees and a better product for our users and our customers. This is something we value deeply and we encourage everyone to come be a part of changing the way the industry works.

Practical information
We are a remote-friendly company and operate in a hybrid work model. Your team will be located mainly in Malmö, Stockholm and Budapest and we would love it if you live close to any of those locations - we value the flexibility in being able to meet part of the team quite easily.

Let’s go!

Title: Traineeprogram inom Business Intelligence
Description:
Är du nyexaminerad data- eller systemvetare, civilingenjör eller har motsvarande teknisk utbildning med intresse för data och vill kickstarta din karriär inom Business Intelligence och Data Analytics den 1 september 2023? Då är Business Visions traineeprogram i Stockholm någonting för dig. Vi arbetar med att göra det enkelt för våra kunder att ta beslut genom att bygga moderna dataplattformar för datadrivna organisationer där varje kunds utmaning är unik.
Business Vision är ett BI-konsultföretag med en varm gemenskap och hos oss har du stor möjlighet att forma din egen utveckling då vi har en flexibel och platt organisation med snabba beslutsvägar. För oss är det en självklarhet att främja en hållbar balans mellan arbete och fritid. Vi ser alla våra konsulter och är stolta över att ha skapat en rolig, utvecklande och framåtdrivande kultur. En kultur där vi med våra värdeord mod, hjärta och trovärdighet uppmuntras att våga utmana oss själva att ta nya vägar, värnar om och stöttar både kollegor och kunder, aldrig slutar att vara nyfikna och ständigt strävar efter att bygga sin egen och företagets trovärdighet. Det är tillsammans som vi kan leverera ett värde för våra kunder och kontinuerligt utveckla Business Vision till att fortsätta vara en fantastisk arbetsplats.
Business Vision har sedan september 2014 med stor framgång genomfört traineeprogram vars syfte är att ge en god grund att stå på inför klivet in i BI-konsultbranschen. Traineeprogrammet är en heltidstjänst efter examen där du får lära dig allt om Microsoft Business Intelligence genom mini-projekt, föreläsningar och utbildningar samt följa våra BI-konsulter i deras arbetsdag. Självklart är det dina seniora kollegor som lotsar dig inom hela Microsofts BI-plattform, vilket har lett till att vi har mycket god erfarenhet av att utbilda juniora kollegor.
Traineeprogrammet är en heltidstjänst efter avslutad examen och genomförs på Business Visions kontor i centrala Stockholm.
Oavsett bakgrund vill vi att du ska:
Ha en god analytisk förmåga
Vara lösningsfokuserad
Gilla att programmera
Ha lätt för att samarbeta med andra
Ta initiativ
Ha förmåga att arbeta självständigt
Vara nyfiken
Flytande svenska i både tal och skrift/fluent in both spoken and written Swedish
Det är extra meriterande om du har:
En examen med inriktning inom informations- eller datateknik
Ett intresse för exempelvis SQL, C#, Python och Javascript
Men, för oss är det absolut viktigast att du känner dig bekväm med våra värdeord - mod, hjärta och trovärdighet - då vår kultur präglas starkt av dessa.
För att trivas på Business Vision:
Du är nyfiken, driven och vill alltid fortsätta utvecklas
Du ansvarar för och driver din egen kompetensutveckling
Du strävar efter långsiktiga och öppna relationer
Du är ödmjuk, gillar god gemenskap och antar varje uppdrag med hjärta!
Känner du igen dig i ovanstående beskrivning? Vill du vara en del av ett nytänkande företag med lång erfarenhet och med specialistkompetens inom Business Intelligence och Data Analytics? Varmt välkommen att skicka in en ansökan tillsammans med personligt brev och CV till oss! Vill du veta mer om hur det är att vara trainee på Business Vision kan du läsa mer här eller kontakta vår traineechef Monika för mer information eller frågor: monika.mattsson@businessvision.se.
PS. Kika in vår Instagram för att få en inblick i hur det är att arbeta hos oss
‍
Varmt välkommen att skicka in din ansökan idag!

Title: Senior Manager - Visa Consulting and Analytics
Description:
Company Description

Visa is a world leader in digital payments, facilitating more than 215 billion payments transactions between consumers, merchants, financial institutions and government entities across more than 200 countries and territories each year. Our mission is to connect the world through the most innovative, convenient, reliable and secure payments network, enabling individuals, businesses and economies to thrive.
When you join Visa, you join a culture of purpose and belonging – where your growth is priority, your identity is embraced, and the work you do matters. We believe that economies that include everyone everywhere, uplift everyone everywhere. Your work will have a direct impact on billions of people around the world – helping unlock financial access to enable the future of money movement.
Join Visa: A Network Working for Everyone.

Job Description

Visa Consulting and Analytics (VC&A) drives tangible, impactful and financial results for Visa’s network clients, including both financial services and merchants. Drawing on our expertise in strategy consulting, data analytics, brand management, marketing, operational and macroeconomics, Visa Consulting and Analytics solves the most strategic problems for our clients.
The Nordics and Baltics (N&B) Consulting Practice within VC&A provides consulting and solution services for Visa’s issuer, acquirers and merchants in the Nordics and Baltics. We apply our deep expertise in the payments industry to provide solutions to assist clients with their key business priorities drive growth and improve profitability.
The team is looking for a Consultant to join our strategic consulting practice and play a role developing high impact projects for Visa’s clients in the N&B region. This role is delivering and implementing projects and solutions and will develop initiatives to promote sustainable and profitable growth, thereby ensuring that Visa is both, the preferred brand and unique business partner.
Typical projects may include -
How does an issuer expand or increase market share in consumer market?
How should a credit card issuer use emerging technology to acquire the best customers?
How does an issuer expand their credit card portfolio while mitigating credit risk?
How does an issuer optimize their revenues?
How do we enable increases spend in specific segments?
What we expect of you, day to day.
Be part of the team delivering consulting initiatives and contributes to closing engagement by identifying potential opportunities with large banks/financial institutions.
Identify solutions and actionable insights that will help clients to grow their portfolios
Partner with peers in other functional areas (e.g., sales and solutions, marketing, sales, risk, innovation, products) and across global regional teams to execute projects in ways that leverage the breadth and depth of Visa’s resources
Proactively engage with Visa leaders in regular strategic & planning discussions cultivate and manage a pipeline of work with FIs (Financial Institutions).
Produce insights, analyses and recommendations to improve client performance, boost growth, drive understanding of client issues and provide strategic guidance for client priorities across the verticals and segments.

Qualifications

What we're after...
Previous experience at a large management consulting firm or similar role at Banks/FIs
Experience working with financial indicators to measure business performance with a focus on impacting ROI and excellent analytical skills, with the ability to use data to convey a clear message to clients and the business
Ability to solve business problems through data driven methodologies and proficiency in some leading-edge analytic and business intelligence tools
Self-motivated, results oriented individual with the ability to handle numerous projects concurrently
Excellent communication, story-telling and presentation skills and a great team player
Technology mindset, curious, up-to-date with digital trends and applications
Ability to travel up to 30%

Additional Information

Flex Work Arrangement - Hybrid Position - This is a hybrid position. Hybrid employees can alternate time between both remote and office. Employees in hybrid roles are expected to work from the office two days a week, Tuesdays and Wednesdays with a general guidepost of being in the office 50% of the time based on business needs.
Visa is an EEO Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability or protected veteran status. Visa will also consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with EEOC guidelines and applicable local law.

Title: Analytics Manager
Description:
About the job

Are you an expert in Procurement and data analytics? And are you able to secure the connection of Procurement to the Analytics Platform, giving us access to a wealth of information? Then you may be our new Analytics Manager!
As an Analytics Manager, you will enable Procurement to work with Vattenfall’s Analytics Platform while improving the solutions we currently have. You will support Procurement and the business with a thorough understanding of the data that we have, with the acquisition of new data and consequently the use of new insights to improve results. And you will be our numbers guru driving the understanding of our Procurement business and driving our value delivery with continuous improvement.
You will provide Procurement with easily accessible information and insights that will support our staff in their daily responsibilities. Next to this, we would like to use available and new data to increase predictability of procurement processes and results with new machine learning-driven technologies. We continuously aim to increase efficiency and effectiveness of Procurement. The Analytics Manager will help us achieve this via smarter usage of data, the implementation of new solutions that will improve our information and insights, via new solutions and new channels.
Your responsibilities:
Being the SPOC for Vattenfall Finance and IT for the connection of Procurement to the Vattenfall Analytics Platform and for improvements to current solutions.
Supporting Procurement on a day-to-day basis with all requests relating to data, information, and insights.
Supporting Procurement on a day-to-day basis with all requests relating to dashboards, performance, and continuous improvement initiatives.
Support Procurement’s Digital Transformation program with project management of all data related activities and with value management as owner of the business case solution for the program.
Work with the data analyst in program and day-to-day business activities and provide guidance and coaching.
Identifying current gaps and omissions and designing solutions for key strategic projects across the business.
Redesign the Procurement Lab into a steady provider of solutions where new (data) technologies are being applied to solve business problems and create business opportunities.
Work together with partner and stakeholders to create a data architecture, and select the right tools to optimize this data landscape incl the tools needed to achieve Procurement goals.
Location
This position could be done from: Stockholm, Amsterdam Berlin or London.

Your profile

Your profile / who are you?
You have extensive experience in Procurement and know source-to-contract and procure-to-pay process in detail (including SAP). You speak data language and can translate the information needs of Procurement to requirements for those working with Procurement Data. Your data engineering and science skills are at a high level, and you are an absolute numbers guru driving the understanding and continuous improvement of what Procurement does. You have strong experience executing this in either an Agile way of working or in traditional project management methodologies, are organized, pro-active and results oriented, with excellent communication and collaboration skills.
Next to this, you recognize yourself in the following:
Minimum of 5 years of experience working in a similar Procurement role or in consultancy in which you helped digital transformations of Procurement, systems implementations and/or worked in the data and analytics space for Procurement connecting Procurement units to Analytics platforms, integrating external data sources, and working with cloud-based solutions.
Extensive knowledge of ERP software (SAP is a must) and Procurement tools in general.
Extensive knowledge of the analytics industry, developments in the industry and application of new technologies for (Procurement) Analytics purposes.
Exceptional problem solving, and modeling skills with ability to synthesize and analyze data to create useful information and concise analysis.
Can work autonomously, to meet tight deadlines, and to thrive in a fast-paced environment under pressure.
Ability to work collaboratively across functions and develop strong relationships with business leaders
Advanced knowledge of Excel, PowerBI, QlikView, Python, SQL and/or other analytical tools. The ability to learn, analyze and implement new systems quickly
Excellent communication skills (both written and verbal) in English

Additional information

Our offer
Good remuneration, a challenging and international work environment, and the possibility to work with some of the best in the field. You will be working in interdisciplinary teams and you can always count on support from committed colleagues. We offer attractive employment conditions and opportunities for personal and professional development.

More Information
We welcome your application in English, no later than the 5th of February. We kindly request that you do not send applications by any means other than via our website as we cannot guarantee that we will be able to process applications that are not made via our website.

For more information about the recruitment process you are welcome to contact our recruiter Stijn van der Kleij via stijn.vanderkleij@vattenfall.com.
At Vattenfall we are convinced that diversity contributes to build a more profitable and attractive company and we strive to be good role model regarding diversity. Vattenfall works actively for all employees to have the same opportunities and rights regardless of gender, ethnicity, age, transgender identity or expression, religion or other belief, disability or sexual orientation.

We look forward to receiving your application!

About the company

Vattenfall is a European energy company with approximately 20 000 employees. For more than 100 years we have electrified industries, supplied energy to people’s homes and modernized our way of living through innovation and cooperation. We now want to make fossil-free living possible within one generation. To be able to reach this ambitious goal we are looking for talented individuals who, in addition to their passion for their own role, also have strong team spirit and want to contribute to supporting a meaningful corporate mission.

Title: Junior consultants to KPMG Management Consulting
Description:
Are you striving to work with highly strategic and digital transformation projects that truly make a difference for top clients? Join us at KPMG Management Consulting! We are growing rapidly and offer great career opportunities.
When working at KPMG Management Consulting you will be part of a global organization and work within various industries and areas, together with competent and inspiring colleagues. As Management Consultants, we advise our clients in their digital transformation journeys from strategy and design to change management and value realization. We work shoulder-to-shoulder with top executives, and we always seek digital, innovative and sustainable solutions to our clients’ business challenges.
Management Consulting
At Management Consulting, you will become part of a group of about 250 colleagues with broad competence and expertise within advisory services across multiple sectors and functions. We work in an environment which combines KPMG’s global network with the local expertise of our employees, a combination that enables us to deliver industry leading support for our clients.
We offer transformation capabilities for complex situations and provide support in e.g., digitalization and technology driven change, company integrations and separations, business transformation and functional improvements, sustainability initiatives and cost reduction & efficiency improvement activities.
Our teams include:
Strategy & Operations – combines several areas of expertise to transform and optimize our customers' core businesses.
Finance Transformation – future-proofs our clients’ finance functions, with expertise in e.g. steering models and processes, strategies and business development, finance and business controlling.
Technology Transformation – operates in the intersection between business and technology, where we support our clients’ digital transformations from strategy to implementation.
Customer Transformation – provides expertise in customer behavior and innovation – with our tools and methods, the team helps companies design the optimal customer experience and strategies for front office functions.
Cyber Security – enables our clients to succeed in their digital transformations by identifying and mitigating their cyber related risks.
Lighthouse – leverages data, analytics and artificial intelligence technologies to build and deliver solutions that transform the business of our clients.
You find more information about our different teams on our website: https://home.kpmg/se/sv/home/campaigns/2020/11/valkommen-till-kpmg-och-var-digitala-monter/advisory.html
What do we offer?
Together with other KPMG colleagues you will be working on exciting client engagements. During your first years at KPMG Management Consulting, you will be a part of our learning and development program Talent Growth. In the program, you will acquire knowledge about business sectors, industry trends and KPMG’s customers. You will learn our tools and methods, gain deep knowledge about our capabilities and delivery models, while also improving your leadership and sales skills. Furthermore, you will get a mentor and a dedicated performance manager supporting you in your career.

Title: Business & Process Development Leader (Insourcing), Customer Fulfilment
Description:
What you'll need to have

We at Ingka are looking to transform how we are set up as an omnichannel retailer, to provide excellent first and last-mile service to our customers, securing both people, planet, and business interests. With the last mile, we mean deliveries to our customer’s homes. The first mile happens when we pick up goods, as the first step in the journey for returning, recycling, and reusing. As part of our IKEA Retail Direction, one of our jobs is to create affordable services to make IKEA convenient (Job 4). We continue to grow in our online sales and services and need to transform the last and first mile to secure our future as an omnichannel retailer.

You are motivated by improving the IKEA business and customer needs and influencing the improvement of the business with a focus on customer satisfaction by leading through co-creation with colleagues and other IKEA units. You are highly interested in the mix of strategic thinking and driving solution development. Independent and interdependent work energizes you, and you enjoy working across functions in an agile way to drive change.

Skills that would benefit you in this role:

Experience leading within the last mile and service fulfillment operations and/or sourcing to provide excellence in operations resulting in a seamless shopping experience.
Experience in in-house operations for the last mile and services from the retail or transportation/logistics industry.
Excellent knowledge of supply chain processes, precisely last mile & service operations, leading to excellent customer fulfillment.
Good leadership in change management and leading in the unknown - a forward-leaning approach and being open to thinking outside the box and challenging how we do things today.
Good at building relationships across the organisation.
Broad knowledge of identifying and involving relevant stakeholders in a project, process, or question to make things happen in a matrix organisation.

Your responsibilities

We seek Business and Process Development Leaders to join our Last & First-mile project team. The project will focus on creating new ways of working, tools, procedures, operating methods, and solutions supported and enabled by a modern and efficient digital landscape.

You will enable IKEA to transform by leading, coordinating, and supporting transformation activities in the area of insourced last mile and service operations. This will include:

Planning and execution of pilot(s) together with co-creation countries & global stakeholders across Ingka – focusing on operational excellence.
Consolidation of best practices in the IKEA retail countries where locally insourced solutions exist today, together with best practices from the industry.
Proactively identifying and clustering business development needs, process improvements, and data analytics needs based on the everyday need of co-workers.
Responsible for documentation (process maps, customer journey's working documentation, measurement specifications, and learning material, and SOPs) to prepare for scaling.
Being an integral part of the line organisation to secure competence sharing, decision-making grounded in reality, and closeness to the IKEA retail countries.

The location for this role is Malmö or Amsterdam. This role requires some travel (depending on the prioritized activities) and is a temporary assignment until 2024-08-31.

Together as a team

Customer Fulfilment (CFF) is a core function within Retail Operations and a fundamental part of making IKEA Omnichannel retailing a reality. This we do by developing and operating replenishment and fulfillment end-to-end with a process-oriented organization, with radical collaboration with our colleagues within Commercial/Market Support, Digital, and Expansion.

We lead with a clear focus on people development and sustainable and cost-effective operations. In everything we do – we have a customer obsession with the aim of achieving 100% Happy Customers.

Questions and support? Let's connect!

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please feel free to contact the Recruiter, Talita Moraes Olsen, at talita.moraes.olsen@ingka.ikea.com. If you have any questions about the role, please get in touch with Alastair Morgan at alastair.morgan@ingka.ikea.com or Sebastian Krysén at sebastian.krysen1@ingka.ikea.com.

Studies show that members of underrepresented communities don’t apply for jobs unless they’re 100% “qualified”. If this is part of the reason you hesitate to apply, we would like you to reconsider and give it a chance. Maybe your profile fits our needs much better than you think. We look forward to receiving your application.

From: “Why Women Don’t Apply for Jobs Unless They’re 100% Qualified” by Tara Sophia Mohr, August 2014”

We look forward to receiving your application in English as soon as possible but no later than the 10th of February 2022.

PLEASE NOTE
Please respect that due to GDPR we cannot review any applications coming to us in other ways than through our recruitment program.

Title: Customer Experience Specialist
Description:
Customer Experience Specialist to Unilever Nordics
Located in Customer Operations, the Customer Experience Specialist at Unilever Nordics creates and optimize our processes. The purpose of this role is to utilize data and costumer insights, driving next-level experience for our customers.
What you will be doing?
Working closely with customers and using data analytics to get insights on customer behavior and processes
Integrating new customers and channels into existing processes in close alignment with our Customer Development teams
Evaluating cost to serve efficiency and cost inefficiencies from ordering behavior
Continuous identification and mapping of improvement processes, managing the quality of customer development
In this role you are the first point of contact for questions related to Customer Experience and our order-to-cash and order-to-delivery areas. You provide input and participate in improvement projects as subject matter expert or project leader. By analyzing data and cooperating with customers and other stakeholders you identify possible improvements and execute plans to enhance Customer Experience performance.
You will work at our Swedish Office in Solna. We offer a hybrid workplace environment with flexibility and self-responsibility. This is a permanent full-time position.
Experience and skills
1-3 years’ experience in similar role within Customer Operations.
Excellent collaborative, communicative and stakeholder management skills
Experienced user in different systems and an analytical mindset. Meritorious to have worked with SAP
Fluent Swedish, both written and spoken. Merit to speak Finnish.
Apply today!
Don’t wait, submit your CV in English online today but by the 3rd of February at the latest. Note that we do not take email applications.
For this role we apply an on-going screening process. The position can therefore be filled before last application date.
Contact
Should you require additional information about this position, please contact hiring manager Karolina Yousef
Karolina.yousef@unilever.com
Should you require additional information about the application process, please contact our Talent Advisor team
ta.nordic@unilever.com
Unilever is an organisation committed to equity, inclusion and diversity to drive our business results and create a better future, every day, for our diverse employees, global consumers, partners, and communities. We believe a diverse workforce allows us to match our growth ambitions and drive inclusion across the business. At Unilever we are interested in every individual bringing their ‘Whole Self’ to work and this includes you! Thus if you require any support or access requirements, we encourage you to advise us at the time of your application so that we can support you through your recruitment journey.

Title: Backend Developer (Data & Analytics)
Description:
Are you a skilled backend developer with great interest in BI, data and analytics?
Integration and data are core components in our unique SaaS service and we are now looking for someone who can build and further develop our data collection and source insight and analytics for our users. You will be a part of a distributed, cross functional team where designers, project leaders and developers all work closely together towards our common goal. Your work will be highly integrated and a key component in our product roadmap.

About SP_CE
83 percent of all business between companies (B2B) is done by people as a result of a number of meetings that over time build trust and relationship. Until the pandemic, these were mainly physical meetings, but in March 2020, everything changed. All of a sudden, fragrant coffee in the conference room and fantastic product presentations were moved into dark Zoom or Team windows.
Analyzes from McKinsey and Gartner state that we will now experience lasting behavioral changes and the prediction is that as much as 80 percent of the interaction between buyers and sellers in B2B will be virtual by 2025. Even with a vaccinated population, up to 60 percent of sales meetings will be virtual already post-pandemic. This means that in principle all sales organizations need to be transformed and develop new capabilities to enchant the buyer digitally. Our belief is that this purely is impossible, or at least difficult, with existing tools that are not optimized for the purpose. In addition, there is a now, on a global, digital market, a need to strengthen the brand in every interaction with the buyer.
Imagine a room where all the meetings take place. Where all material is gathered and where each meeting can be recorded and transcribed automatically. Where both buyers and sellers always can go back along a timeline and see what was said. And where the whole experience is WOW! This is SP_CE.
Meetings become both more efficient and more professional with an unique agenda functionality that seamlessly opens the right camera, the right presentation, the right video at the right time. SP_CE makes the sales meetings interactive and engaging with exploratory questions and a built-in functionality where users can at any time drag and drop a PDF, presentation, or video that they want to discuss and focus on, right there and then.
With SP_CE, companies can also create their own meeting templates and agendas with ready-made content that is shared in the organization, which helps new salespeople to be productive from the first day at work. SP_CE can be integrated with Salesforce, Hubspot or any other CRM system, making the platform a natural extension of the sales process.
About the role
We are looking for a senior backend developer with a keen interest in data. As a developer at SP_CE you will be a part of a distributed, cross functional team where designers, project leaders and developers all work closely to bring valuable data to users . Besides developing and enhancing our platform, you will focus on data integration strategies, build robust end-to-end integrations wit and enabling insight analytics for our end users.
You report to our CTO and receive support from great colleagues in engineering, product and design. Welcome to an extraordinary journey together with team designed for collaboration and collective learning.
What you will do
Develop our data collection and our backend core services
Develop, integrate and use AI-based services to analyze and provide insights from data collected – both post event and in real time.
Analyze and build our insight & analytics layer for both end users and admins.
Inspire and bring the data mindset into everything we do.

Who are you?
We think you are an experienced .NET developer with a degree in computer science, data analytics, mathematics or another relevant field. You have good knowledge of system integrations and data analytics. Maybe you have worked with big data analytics or interested in developing your skills around it.
Do you have these skills?
NET CORE
SQL
NET Web API (REST)
Knowledgeable in data structures and algorithms
Experience with cloud development (Azure/AWS/GCP)
Experience with Microservices architecture
CI/CD
If you have any of these skills you can make an even bigger impact:
Big Data platforms and Analytics Tools
Experience with Kubernetes
AI and sentiment analytics
Type of employment
Full time

Location
We live as we preach and are a Remote & Global Team. You can therefore live wherever you want and work from home. If you are based in Stockholm you also have the option to work on-site in our own office at Convendum Katarinavägen in Stockholm, or at one of Convendum’s different co-working places in Stockholm.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Do you want to be a part of a new Analytics Operations team and get to work in an inspiring environment? Then you should keep reading!
DevPort are now looking for a Data Analyst to join our clients new Analytics Operations team. The Analytics Operations team should act as a catalyst and take responsibility for analytics value creation in all phases; from early ideation with stakeholders to creating runtime dashboards and data pipelines or guiding superusers to help them create their own dashboards. We also cooperate with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to run AI/ML models in operations. The Analytics Operations team is new and as such you will be part of developing the unit and creating successful use cases.
Our clients new Data, Analytics & AI organization is focused on unleashing the value of data collected from connected customer assets. The team are set out to drive the transformation into a data driven culture, where Data, Analytics & AI/ML are an integral part in their services and internal processes. By spanning across Data Foundation, Data Analytics and Data Science they can provide their stakeholders with actionable insights and take ownership of the whole process from ideation and exploration to analytics operations.

About the role
Drive the data journey by connecting with stakeholders, running workshops, identify opportunities and take it from idea to value.
Develop state-of-the art solutions, dashboards, and insight reports.
Stay at the forefront in the analytics space and share knowledge and experience with colleagues.

Your profile
You have a degree in a relevant field or practical experience from utilizing data to drive change.
You are a creative, entrepreneurial problem-solver with an inquisitive attitude and are not afraid of complex challenges or unconventional approaches.
You routinely use dashboarding as a tool for problem solving, and are experienced in at least one dashboarding solution (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, QuickSight, Grafana).
You confidently and systematically build analysis approaches from scratch, including data extraction, scripting and/or programming in relevant languages and analysis with creation of informative and appealing visualizations.
You are a communicative person that builds and maintains trust with stakeholders and colleagues.
Humorous; because, in the end, working in the team should be fun.

What can we offer you?
You will be part of a highly skilled analytics team that together with our stakeholders creates great value in short- and long-term engagements. In this team you will be able to make a data-driven impact on sustainable transport solutions for our client, their customers and society at large - and have fun while doing it. Your workplace will be based in Lindholmen in Gothenburg.

Application
Apply by following the steps below. If you have any questions regarding the position, send an email to Elin Thulin at elin.thulin@devport.se
I am looking forward to read you application!

About DevPort
DevPort is a technology consulting company in an expansive development phase with headquarter in Gothenburg and offices in Stockholm, Linköping, Helsingborg and Karlskrona. DevPort has its core competence in the automotive industry and employs more than 500 people in three business areas - Digital solutions, production development and product development.
We are proud of our employees and of collaborating with several of the world's leading vehicle manufacturers, companies in the defense industry and other development-intensive industries.
We are characterized by a family culture with entrepreneurship, competence, security and a community that infuses the company's operations and contributes to a pleasant and inspiring workplace.

Title: Director Quality
Description:
Candela’s ultimate purpose is to speed up the transition to fossil fuel-free lakes and oceans. We strive to re-think efficiency in marine transportation to radically push the performance boundaries of electric boats and ships.
By combining sensors, computers and advanced submerged hydrofoils, our electric craft flies above the water, reaching speeds and range previously attained only by fossil fuel powerboats.
After launching Candela C-7, Europe’s currently best-selling electric boat, we launched Candela C-8 in August 2021, the first electric boat intended for high volume production. We are also venturing into public transport with the revolutionary foiling P-12 ferry, built for the city of Stockholm.
We are now looking for a Director Quality to support Candela’s growth ambitions. The Director Quality will lead the implementation of culture and practice excellence throughout the entire value chain of the organization, to secure high-quality output.
We are now looking for a manager to lead the quality development and governance at Candela. You are welcomed into fast growing company where you have a great opportunity to develop your own role and team.

Your responsibilities
Manage a team of quality specialists as well as the global responsibility for the quality processes
Internal audits, non-conformance management and quality data analytics
Drive continuous improvements together with your team
Implementation of quality processes
Strong emphasis on hands on quality work - working with production/site managers as well R&D functions
Define and implement Q-standards adapted to local markets where needed
Ability to capture key quality KPIs
Evaluate and follow up the project quality requirements in conjunction with the engineering team
Review suppliers’ inspection test plan and all QA/QC documentation


Your background
You are a leader who likes working with developing, motivating, and coaching your team
Bachelor or Master’s in Engineering, preferably Manufacturing, Process or Quality management
Several years of experience from quality management
Strong personal operational experience within quality management, preferably from the manufacturing industry
Proven track record of running quality projects in a manufacturing environment, with high demands on technical understanding, in a successful way
We highly value your personality and see that you have a positive and pro-active mindset and like to work in teams
You are a good communicator, structured and analytical
+10 years of experience from working with quality
Good to have
Good understanding of Six Sigma and Lean manufacturing concepts
Knowledge of ISO standards 9001, 14001, 45001


Join a stellar team
By bringing together some of the world’s brightest researchers and engineers, we are pushing the boundaries of marine transportation. We take great pride in building engagement within our teams. Our internal motto is “with a revolutionary spirit and kindness”, which translates into an open and honest work environment.
We are a 150+, multinational team of experts within dynamic modelling, hardware design, hydrodynamics, control theory, machine learning, structural engineering work and production to build the next generation of waterborne transport.
This is a full-time position working from our headquarter in Frihamnen as well as our production facility in Rotebro. Working language is English, if you also know Swedish it will be a benefit for yourself, but it is not a prerequisite for the role.

Application
The selection and interview process is ongoing, so send your application in English as soon as it’s ready. Kindly note that we cannot process applications sent via email.
We welcome the opportunity to meet you!

Title: Manager within Data & Analytics
Description:
BearingPoint’s Data & Analytics team combine broad business understanding with deep technology expertise to help our clients make insight driven decisions on all levels of their organization. We help our clients explore the full potential of their data using modern tools and technologies. To meet current and future clients’ needs we are looking to strengthen our team with a Manager with a passion for both business and technology who will be responsible for delivering projects and developing our business within Data & Analytics. The position is based in Stockholm.
We would like to see following in our new colleagues’ profile:
Passion for technology and transforming data to business value
6+ years in consulting delivering projects and developing business
Significant hands on experience with advanced analytics, business intelligence, and/or data warehousing
Experience with advising clients on topics related to data strategy, data governance, and/or building Data & Analytics teams
Experience with SQL, Python, or similar tools in a Data & Analytics context
Master’s degree with excellent academic record
Excellent communication skills both written and spoken
Fluency in Swedish and English (both written and spoken)
Ability to travel if necessary
Our new colleague can expect following from us:
A unique opportunity to carry out challenging Data & Analytics projects including both strategic advisory and business-oriented data science
Exciting career opportunities and possibilities to learn and grow as fast as you desire
Highly competent and down-to-earth colleagues
An informal and “Easy to work with” culture
Competitive compensation and benefits
If this sounds interesting, then we would be happy to receive an application (CV and personal letter) from you. The selection and interview process are ongoing, so we would appreciate your application at your earliest convenience.
About BearingPoint
BearingPoint is an independent management and technology consultancy firm with European roots and a global reach. The company operates in three units: Consulting, Solutions and Ventures. Consulting covers the advisory business; Solutions provides the tools for successful digital transformation, regulatory technology and advanced analytics; Ventures drives the financing and development of start-ups. BearingPoint’s clients include many of the world’s leading companies and organizations. The firm has a global consulting network with more than 10,000 people and supports clients in over 75 countries, engaging with them to achieve measurable and sustainable success.

Title: ERP Data Analytics Architect
Description:
Are you a person who knows how to work with data, and how to design and implement data analytics solutions helping users to realize business value out of data?
Do you want to be a part of an exciting global transport transformation journey at Scania?
We are looking for a Data Analytics Architect who will help us to define the strategy for analytics, build sustainable and reliable framework and best practises for developing business intelligence solutions based on leading technologies from SAP, Microsoft and others.
You will
be a member of an international, multicultural team of passionate professionals working daily in our business and digital core transformation projects
define high level analytics strategy and roadmap
evaluate various SAP and non-SAP analytics solutions (eg. SAP BW/4 HANA, SAP Analytics Cloud, SAP Data Intelligence, Microsoft cloud BI solutions)
design architecture of advanced analytics solutions on top of data coming from different enterprise applications and big data sources
support business users in the evaluation of different methodologies, technologies and ways of working
be engaged in the design and implementation of a common analytics solution – from collection of data helping understand business requirements to implementation of solutions helping business users to realize value from data
participate in design and build of a sustainable and reliable framework and best practises in the area of data analytics with the use of SAP, Microsoft and other technologies
mentor colleagues in the company on how Scania can become more data-driven and efficient with the use of proposed analytics solutions
In order to succeed in this role, we also see that you
have proven experience as data analytics architect and several years of professional experience in data analytics
have been working in large scale SAP implementation projects
have experience in design and implementation of SAP analytics solutions, including cloud based services
can provide a deep SAP functional and technical expertise in the data analytics area
can provide leadership and guidance to other colleagues working with data analytics – from business teams and implementation partners
may have experience from the automotive industry – that would be an advantage
have good social skills allowing you to communicate with stakeholders in different parts of our company
have excellent communication skills in English, communication in Swedish is an added plus
Questions?
If you would like to find out more about the position, please contact Jakub Zurek (Group Manager),+46-8-553 736 63. A background check will be a part of the recruitment.
Attach your CV to apply. We are looking forward to your application!
About Scania
Scania is a world-leading provider of transport solutions. Together with our partners and customers we are driving the shift towards a sustainable transport system. In 2021, we delivered 88,930 trucks, 4,436 buses as well as 11,786 industrial and marine power systems to our customers. Net sales totalled to over SEK 146 billion, of which over 20 percent were services related. Founded in 1891, Scania now operates in more than 100 countries and employs some 54,000 people. Research and development are mainly concentrated in Sweden. Production takes place in Europe and Latin America with regional product centres in Africa, Asia and Eurasia. Scania is part of TRATON GROUP. For more information visit: www.scania.com.

Title: Data Engineer - Göteborg
Description:
Enfo som en av de ledande tjänsteleverantörna inom Data & Analytics i Skandinavien är i en expansionsfas. Vi förstärker nu vårt vassa team i Göteborg. Hos oss får du sitta i fräscha lokaler centralt i stan med stor frihet när det kommer till hur och vart du vill jobba.
I rollen som Data Engineer hos oss kommer du att designa, modellera och integrera data från både strukturerade och ostrukturerade datakällor. Du kommer att bygga dataflöden och dataarkitektur.
Inom Enfo Data & analytics är vi 150 specialister som hjälper våra kunder med rådgivning, design och implememtation av Analyticslösningar, oftast i molnet och stöttade av våra avdelningar inom cybersäkerhet och integration. Vi har också ett nära samarbete med våra produktpartners som Microsoft, Snowflake, Data Bricks och Tibco bland andra.
Vem är du?
Du har erfarenhet att bygga och optimera senaste generationens analyticslösningar och vill fortsätta utvecklas inom detta område:
Minimum 3 års erfarenhet av ETL
Minimum 2 års erfarenhet av Azure (Data Factory, Data lake, SQL)
Praktisk erfarenhet av Databricks, Snowflake
Kunskap inom Matillion och DBT är meriterande

Du har relevant högskoleutbildning och du kan svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift. Arbetet hos oss genomsyras av en lärande kultur och arbete i team samt frihet under ansvar.

Väx med oss - sök redan idag!
Ansök genom att skicka in ditt CV samt en motivering till varför du är intresserad av att jobba hos oss. Vi arbetar med löpande urval så passa på att skicka in din ansökan snarast möjligt då vi kan komma att stänga processen innan sista ansökningsdag. Vi ser fram emot din ansökan!

Title: Analytics Engineer
Description:
At Epidemic Sound we are reinventing the music industry. Our carefully curated catalog, with over 35,000 tracks, is tailored for storytellers, streaming services, and in-store soundtracks. Countless clients around the world, from broadcasters, production companies, DSPs, and YouTubers rely on our tracks to help them tell their stories. Epidemic Sound’s music is heard in hundreds of millions of online videos daily, across millions of playlist streams, and in thousands of in-store locations. Headquartered in Stockholm, we’re spread across offices in New York City, Los Angeles, Seoul, Hamburg, and Amsterdam. We’re growing fast, have lots of fun, and are taking the music industry with us.
We’re now looking for an Analytics Engineer to join our central Data engineering team, the team that is responsible for our Data Platform. You will play a vital role in ingesting data from our data lake into the data warehouse, where data will be transformed, scheduled, and made ready to be used for analytics & product development teams. You might come from a background where you have passion for Data Modeling or Data Engineering. Or you might have worked as a Data Scientist or Data Analyst and you’re curious and want to work more with Data Engineering.
In order for you to thrive in this role, we believe that you have one or more of the following:
Experience in SQL and Python
A strong interest and curiosity in data – you might have also worked with large-scale data warehouses like BigQuery or Snowflake, data modelling, and/or relational model design
Experience in any of the following tooling: Terraform, Snowplow, Apache Airflow, Fivetran, Looker, OpsGenie
Experience with cloud computing such as GCP or AWS
You definitely have the following:
A love for teamwork
A love for continuous improvement and learning
Follow best software engineering practices in your work
The ability to communicate in English with professional working proficiency
You value best practices but realize that all rules have exceptions
A passion for sharing your knowledge and teaching others what you know
Nice to have experience:
dbt
Previous experience working with or setting up ELT-like data pipelines

How you will make an impact
You would join Epidemic’s Data Engineering team, with a mission to provide the platform, tools, solutions, and data sets that enable the company to stay ever more data-informed. As an Analytics Engineer, you would play a key role in bridging Data Engineering and Data Analytics.
Our modern data stack runs on Google Cloud Platform and part of our solution stack includes BigQuery as a data warehouse, Google Cloud Composer (Airflow) for data pipeline orchestration, Dataflow jobs for data processing, and dbt for data transformation.

You can expect to:
Join an organization with passionate Data Scientists and Data Engineers at an early stage of the company's history. This is a chance to be part of building a data analytics platform that scales worldwide
Design, build and maintain the Epidemic data models
Drive data architecture matters, including following the data definition and data modeling principles across all parts of the business, and ensuring that everything from tracking to reporting cubes adheres to Epidemic’s best practices
Act as a stakeholder and partner with both engineering teams and analytics teams to deliver well-defined, tested, and high-quality data sets
Work with business stakeholders and design data models to quantitatively support everything from corporate strategy to user acquisition
Support and mentor analytics consumers on best software engineering practices
This role will include finding ways to share learnings across the organization. It could be via internal talks, writing internal blog posts, or any other way you may think of. You can also expect to learn a ton of new things, be it through hack-days, courses, conferences, or tech talks. We emphasize learning and we also expect you to share your knowledge with your colleagues.
We collaborate constantly and are big believers in teamwork and the value of practices like careful code reviews and pair (or mob) programming. On top of this, you can expect to have lots of fun and take pride in what you and all of Epidemic is doing.

Curious to learn more about who we are and what we do? Check out our brand new "About us" page https://www.epidemicsound.com/about-us/

We have lots of fun soundtracking the world and our annual Spring Bash is an event that captures this perfectly. Take a look at our most recent one, a virtual celebration!

Application
Do you want to be a part of our fantastic team? Please apply, in English, by clicking the link below.
We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business, and a better world. We value diversity and encourage everyone to come and soundtrack the world with us.

Title: BI-Consultant Graduate Program
Description:
twoday Analytics är ett av bolagen i twoday-koncernen som fokuserar på Data Analytics och Visualization med hjälp av moderna system som Power BI, Qlik Sense och TimeXtender. Detta innefattar arbete med frontendutveckling, utveckling av dashboards, rapportering och self service BI-lösningar. Just nu söker vi nyexaminerade deltagare till vårt Graduate Program!
Vad erbjuds du som Graduate?
Som deltagare i vårt Graduate Program kommer du tidigt vara med och utveckla BI-lösningar åt våra kunder. Du kommer att ingå i ett team som besitter djup kunskap i beslutsstöd, affärsstyrning och projektledning. Din roll kommer att vara konsultativ och direkt mot kund. Du kommer b.la att få arbeta i olika kunduppdrag med att designa, integrera och modellera data från olika datakällor.
Som Graduate tilldelas du även en personlig mentor som du kommer ha nära kontakt med under hela programmet. Tillsammans med din mentor sätts en tydlig plan för din personliga utveckling utifrån dina mål och preferenser. Inom twoday-koncernen tror vi starkt på ett gränsöverskridande kunskapsutbyte mellan våra olika Graduate Program. Därför ingår det även i programmet att träffa andra deltagare inom koncernen på gemensamma kunskapsträffar och workshops.

Vi söker dig som:
Har en kandidat och/eller masterexamen inom data/systemvetenskap/ekonomi eller annat relevant område
Har ett stort intresse för IT, teknik och verksamhet
Har ett intresse för BI, meriterande med kännedom om olika aktörer inom området
Har ett stort driv och vilja att utvecklas
Grundläggande kunskaper inom databaser eller design och strukturering av datawarehouse samt kunskaper inom web är meriterande
Talar svenska och engelska obehindrat
Vi tror att du som söker rollen drivs av att arbeta kundnära och har lätt för att skapa och behålla goda relationer. Du motiveras av att hålla dig uppdaterad inom BI samt har ett intresse för datavisualisering och problemlösning. För att trivas och lyckas i rollen ser vi att du motiveras av att arbeta självständigt och konsultativt. Att våga ta initiativ och driva på, vara lyhörd och ha en målinriktad approach är egenskaper vi värderar högt.
Ansökan
Visst låter det spännande? Vi genomför urval löpande så vänta inte med att skicka in din ansökan då det finns ett begränsat antal platser. Sista ansökningsdag är 28 februari 2023. Preliminär start för Graduate Program är 14 augusti 2023.
Vid frågor om programmet eller angående din ansökan är du välkommen att kontakta Consulting Manager Robin Smith, robin.smith@twoday.com eller Talent Acquisition Partner Felix Wallin, felix.wallin@twoday.com

Vad erbjuder twoday som arbetsgivare?
Medarbetaren i centrum
twoday är en flexibel arbetsplats med varierande arbetsuppgifter och stort utrymme att utvecklas. Vårt främsta mål är att du som medarbetare kan arbeta i miljö som är trivsam, innovativ, och framförallt - rolig!
Hos oss hittar du ett väl sammansvetsat flexibelt gäng som hjälper varandra och våra kunder att nå framgång varje dag. Med mer än 2000 anställda arbetar vi för att skapa en bättre morgondag, som ger mervärde för oss som människor och samhället som helhet. Vi tror att med rätt medarbetare och högteknologiska lösningar kan vi skapa en tydligare bild av var vi är just nu – och var vi kommer vara imorgon.
Vår starka tillväxt, vår lönsamhet och våra konkurrenskraftiga villkor är något vi är stolta över. Som en av Europas ledande IT-koncerner är det för oss självklart att ligga i framkant inom morgondagens mjukvara för effektivare företag. Vi är idag ledande inom Cloud-teknologi och en stor del av koncernens omsättning återinvesteras årligen i R&D. Just nu pågår det bland annat ökade satsningar inom machine learning, artificiell intelligens och big data i syfte att ytterligare effektivisera våra kunders affärsprocesser.
Vill du vara med oss på denna resa?

Mångfald & inkludering
Möter du inte varje krav? Studier har visat att kvinnor och andra underrepresenterade grupper är mindre benägna att ansöka till ett jobb om dom inte möter varje kvalifikation. På twoday är vi dedikerade att bygga en arbetsplats som genomsyras av mångfald och inkludering. Om du är exalterad över denna roll men din tidigare erfarenhet inte matchar till hundra procent mot arbetsskrivningen, så uppmanar vi dig att ansöka ändå.
