Title: Master Data Management (MDM) experter
Description:
Till flera nya projekt till våren söker vi nu erfarna konsulter inom MDM – Master Data management. För dessa spännande projekt behöver vi stärka upp vårt MDM-team med både utvecklare, projektledare och Business Analysts.
Hos oss arbetar några av Nordens främsta experter inom Data, Analytics & AI, vilket ger oss bästa möjliga förutsättningar att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas på sin resa mot ett datadrivet beslutsfattande.
Vi bistår våra uppdragsgivare med datadriven affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling hela vägen från strategiska vägval till implementerad lösning och realiserad nytta.
Hos oss är medarbetarnas utrymme att utvecklas stort och kulturen präglas av frihet under ansvar. För dig som lockas av att vara med i Sveriges vassaste team inom Data, Analytics och AI, är detta ett jobb med framtidsmöjligheter för dig.
Mer om oss:
Capgemini Insights & Data, är Nordens ledare inom Data, AI och Analytics. Vi är över 300 anställda, fördelade på våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö och Helsingborg. Våra tjänster innefattar konsultverksamhet inom Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services och Solution Services. Många av marknadens främsta experter arbetar hos oss, vilket ger oss utmärkta förutsättningar att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas i sin resa mot datadrivna beslut. Vår position på den nordiska marknaden ger oss möjlighet att verkligen göra skillnad för våra kunder, och att erbjuda alltifrån lokala projekt till större globala transformationsprojekt.
Vem du är:
Vi söker nu dig som har flera års erfarenhet inom området MDM – Master Data Management i roller som utvecklare, projektledare och/eller Business Analyst. Du har erfarenhet ifrån ett antal olika MDM projekt och du är van att arbeta med kunder i olika branscher och inom olika funktioner.
Du har gärna en bakgrund som Data Steward med helhetssyn och bred kunskap inom en verksamhets masterdatahantering
Vi ser gärna att du har erfarenhet av att arbeta med olika MDM verktyg, där minst ett av dom är Profisee eller Informatica. Vi tror även att du har lång erfarenhet av att arbeta med SQL.
Det är viktigt att du är analytisk, lösningsorienterad och nyfiken, att du har en god samarbetsförmåga samt lätt för att kommunicera. Du har relevant högskoleutbildning och du kan svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift.

Title: BI Data Specialist
Description:
Are you a skilled and hands-on BI Data Specialist within Business Intelligence? Would you like to be part of Hilding Anders’ transformation journey to becoming a truly consumer focused, digital first, health & wellness company, offering leadership in innovative sleep solutions? Then you may be our new BI Data Specialist who we can offer an exciting career opportunity in a truly international and entrepreneurial environment!

ABOUT THE HILDING ANDERS FAMILY
Hilding Anders is a leading SLEEP company within the health and wellness industry, offering a wide array of products that help people sleep better. As a team of close to 5 000 individuals based across Europe and Asia, we are driven to become the global leader in sleep products and services. With a broad portfolio ranging from luxury & premium to private label and international to local brands, we are proud to deliver sleep products and services for all needs in over 40 countries worldwide. The company is based in Malmö, Sweden, and is majority owned by US based Private Equity firm, KKR. Read more on: www.hildinganders.com/
Group IT
Hilding Anders’ Group IT function focuses on supporting the Group in achieving its’ business objectives. In a global group such as Hilding Anders, exchange of information is key and Group IT oversees and manages information channels, security monitoring and Business Intelligence platforms. The team consists of approximately 10 experienced professionals who work closely together with the Group’s respective local IT managers.
WHAT’S IN IT FOR YOU?
If you want to be a part of our team, using your skills and knowledge within business intelligence, we are happy to tell you that we are looking for a BI Data Specialist to be based at our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden. We offer you a great opportunity to be part of the Hilding Anders transformation journey and our transitioning from being one of the leading bedding & mattress suppliers to becoming a truly consumer focused, digital first, health & wellness company, offering leadership in innovative sleep solutions. You will be part of a fast growing global business!
THE ROLE
We are looking for a BI Data Specialist to join our dynamic Group IT team. This is a specialist role, with clear scope to be involved in all aspects of the work our brilliant team do.
Coming with a strong technical background complemented with finance and/or IT background you will understand business intelligence (BI) and analytics and will be passionate about translating data into actionable insights. The ability to work cross functional is key, as are strong communication skills and the confidence to challenge the status quo.
Responsibilities
You will be the business intelligence partner to several executive or senior managers (mostly finance) within Hilding Anders to understand different data needs and build a solution that delivers high quality and reliable data.
The position includes working closely with Hilding Anders BI users to capture business needs, analysing, designing, developing, testing, and validating new developments.
Handle support issues regarding report changes, validate report outcome with internal system data.
Develop and implement strategies related to Data management and system processes.
Support in creating site specific standardized way of working to secure that the output complies with the data quality.
You will be responsible for presenting and distributing operational data, from the mail and logistics domain.
You will report directly to our Head of IT.
WHO YOU ARE
We believe that the ideal candidate has worked with business intelligence, and has the following qualifications and experiences:
2-4 years of experience within data analysis and/or finance.
Data professional, potentially data engineer, with strong knowledge of relation databases and dataflows.
University degree in relevant field such as computer science, data analytics or finance.
Experience from working with data in a finance setup.
Programming capability in SQL.
Solid experience in understanding and implementing Data Governance, Data modelling together with to ERP-systems M3.
Good understanding of ERP system, M3, processes and to be able to interpret business requirement from local needs.
Working knowledge of Power BI. Report and/or dashboard building. Eye for visualizations.
Important of course is the specific IT and general data capabilities.
We expect you have passionate interest in data warehouse and knowledge of extract, load and transform data from different structured and unstructured data sources.
Expert skills in working with PowerBI and developing PowerApps. Experience in creating advanced dashboards, and reports is also required.
Ability to explain complex and technical concepts.
Fluent in English.
To be the perfect fit for Hilding Anders, we also believe that you are:
a team player and a natural leader with a humble approach.
creative innovative and constantly strive to push behaviors in the business forward.
driven by a purpose and passion to achieve results.
genuine, loyal, naturally inspire others to become the best and value long term relationships .
strategic and operational in your way of working.

Title: Partnership Sales Manager, Sweden
Description:
We strive for creative ways to make people healthier, think outside the box – and are always curious to learn new things and get things done. So join us in our mission for health and become part of one of Europe's fastest-growing health apps - Stepler!

Physical activity has value for the individual, society, and the world. Our mission is to increase movement incentives by gamifying health and reward our users' efforts.
The outcome? - A healthier lifestyle and a happier wallet :)
Do you have what it takes to change our sedentary world once and for all by gamifying health? Then you might fit into our team of talented heroes.
Stepler is both a health and a marketplace app.
We became Scandinavia's fastest-growing health app by providing the best experience to our users and having the best deals on our platform.
Your job will be to find partnerships with brands and companies that align with our mission for health. These partnerships will cover a wide range of product categories and services: Clothing, Personal Care, Beauty, Tech, Jewelry, Food, and many more.
You will be responsible for building and promoting our growing partner ecosystem.

Your daily adventures will include:
Actively seeking out and with excellent interpersonal skills engaging with customer prospects.
Negotiating exclusive deals with consumer brands to place their products and services on Stepler's marketplace
Building and maintaining relationships with leading companies and brands.
Developing new businesses, growing existing ones, and being the representative of Stepler towards our partners.
Maintaining technical expertise and product knowledge necessary to expand sales.
Performing cost-benefit and needs analysis of existing/potential customers to meet their needs
Prospecting for new customers through cold calls and emails
Timely delivering upon agreed sales targets and outcomes
Coordinating sales efforts with team members and other departments
Analyze the territory/market’s potential

To thrive at Stepler, you should:
Be a self-motivated spirit with a strong sense of ownership and a hands-on approach.
Thrive in the fields of ad sales, direct sales, and digital sales
Have strong communication and negotiation skills
Experience with research methods using data analytics software
Be comfortable with developing business frameworks to support your strategies and decisions
Be fluent in Swedish and have excellent communication skills in English
Like to have fun at work and spread positive vibes to your surroundings
And, maybe the most important thing – you are passionate about making the world a healthier place
You will get extra credits for:
Experience in the tech business, startup, or dynamic high-growth company
Experience in project management or running a business

Why you’ll love it here:
Your daily duties will have a meaningful impact on millions of people worldwide.
You’ll work with the most friendly, supportive colleagues in a high talent-density environment.
As we grow, so will you! Stepler’s fast-paced, challenging environment offers you great opportunities for professional development.
A tight team of highly talented colleagues from all over Europe
Did we spark your interest? Apply today!

Title: Data Engineer (Engagement team)
Description:
Pushing boundaries to achieve a sustainable future
The world is dealing with an environmental crisis and energy crisis, and we, as Vargas Holding’s latest venture, are actively creating a sustainable future. We provide renewable energy solutions to everyday homes to help them cut their dependency on oil and gas, electrify their energy consumption, and to control their energy bill. To solve the climate and energy crisis, we are at the forefront of creating innovative solutions that accelerate the creation of smart and sustainable homes.
Heating alone represents some 15% of the EU's CO2 emissions and switching to a sustainable energy solution is by far the easiest way for a household to make a real impact. That's why we are dedicated to developing solutions that not only combat these crises and create sustainable homes but also empower homeowners to take control of their energy consumption and save money on their energy bills.
Our goal is to cut homeowners’ dependency on fossil fuels and help them transition to clean, renewable energy sources. We make it possible for everyone to combat the climate crisis. With a firm belief in the power of innovation and technology, we build solutions for today’s challenges, and for those of tomorrow – for current and our next generations. By transforming local energy consumption, we will create a global transformation.
We are passionate about making a positive impact on the world, and we believe that by creating smart and sustainable homes, we can do just that. We hope you will join us in this important work as we strive to make a difference in the fight against the climate crisis.

About the role
We are expanding our Engagement team where we focus on creating an engaging experience for our customers when they have their energy solution installed at home. We are looking for somebody who can help us create the data structures and models, the operational environment we need to optimize our data analytics and visualization for our users.
You will be responsible for designing and implementing data structures and pipelines to support data-driven features and capabilities for our software application. You will work closely with cross-functional teams including product management, data science, and engineering to understand data requirements and ensure that data is properly collected, cleansed, transformed, stored and served for use in data-driven products and features.
Your other responsibilities include:
Assist with the design, setup, maintenance and support of data pipelines and structures
Participate in the design and development of data-driven products and features
Collaborate with team members to troubleshoot and resolve data-related issues

Who are you
From a technical perspective we would like you to have:
2-3 YoE as a data engineer
Strong understanding of data engineering concepts
Experience working with a variety of data sources and technologies
Experience with data cleansing and transformation, ETL pipelines
Comfort working with large and complex datasets
Familiarity with SQL and other database querying languages
We would even appreciate it if you have some experience with/knowledge of some of the following:
Familiarity with other programming languages such as Java, Kotlin or Python
As a person we would like you to be:
High ambition, initiative, and entrepreneurial mindset (self-starter)
A personality who thrives in an ever-changing environment and can create structure from the ground up
Fast-moving and solution-oriented
Analytical skills

What we offer
Besides a competitive salary and secondary benefits, we offer the opportunity to build a global company and product with true environmental impact. Our team is led by top engineers from IKEA, Volvo, Scania, Viaplay, and Kry, bringing a wealth of experience and expertise to the table.
As a member of our team, you'll have the chance to be a part of a fast-moving growth journey with far-reaching learning and development opportunities. You'll have the chance to work with some of the most talented and innovative professionals in the industry, dedicated to making a positive impact on the world through our products and services. You'll be able to contribute to the development of cutting-edge technology that has the potential to make a significant positive impact on the world.
In addition to the opportunity to contribute to a meaningful and impactful company, you'll also have access to ongoing learning and development opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally. We believe that our team is our greatest asset, and we are committed to fostering a supportive and inclusive culture that empowers our employees to reach their full potential.
Whether you're an experienced professional or just starting out in your career, we believe that everyone has the potential to make a meaningful contribution to our mission. So, if you're passionate about building a better future and want to be a part of something special, we'd love to have you join us. So, come and join our team and be a part of building a truly global company with a product that makes a real difference in the world.
Don't hesitate and send us your application today! If you have any questions regarding applications or else, contact me at rolf.kusch@vargasholding.se

Title: Data Scientist to Froda
Description:
About Froda
Froda was founded in 2015 with a clear vision – to revolutionize the banking experience for entrepreneurs by making it easy and affordable for them to invest in their ideas. Today, we are one of Sweden's fastest growing fintech with major international growth plans. We are a creative tech company with the ambition to turn a historically expensive and unfair industry into something ethical, sustainable, and forward thinking. Behind the company are several well-known investors and talents from e.g., Avanza, Spotify, Google, and Klarna.

About the Role
Froda is at the unique point of taking our data analytics and real-time decisioning to the next level. We are now looking for our next Data Scientist to help us transform our data into actionable insights.

You will design, develop, and maintain statistical data models in collaboration with our chief data scientist as well as our data engineers and analysts. Besides working with modeling you will also build and work on the data pipelines which feed our models. This is a key role in evolving Froda's data strategy as well as in the development and realization of our data platform.

Who are you?
We believe that you are a curious person who enjoys working in a team with other eager and open-minded people, who can’t wait to learn more and share their knowledge. You are driven by finding the right solution, in a business-oriented manner. We want you to be fluent in English and Swedish for this role, and to have a master's degree preferably in engineering, mathematics, or statistical modeling.
When it comes to your tech skills, we believe that you have experience of:
At least a couple of years as a Data Scientist or a similar role,
Working with statistical modeling in either Python, R, or similar,
Working extensively with SQL.
If you also have worked with machine learning, credit modeling, and maybe have programmed some in C#, Java, or similar, it is of course a plus!
So, what’s in it for you?
You will have the opportunity to work hands-on in a fast-paced, exciting, and collaborative scale-up company with ambitious co-workers that also honors the work-life balance. To add an edge to our employee offer we also have a warrant program for everybody working here.
At Froda, you will truly have freedom under responsibility, which means that you will have the ability to impact your own work and tackle a wider set of tasks than in a typical data science role. You have the actual possibilities to impact tech strategy and decisions. We are a passionate team with an open culture, and we truly believe that the best decisions are taken by combining people's knowledge!

If you have any questions or thoughts concerning the role or process, don’t hesitate to send me an email at: anna.sellhed@froda.se.

Title: GLOBAL MARKETING COORDINATOR - STELLANA
Description:
Stellana is a global company which is located in Laxå Sweden. We are a product area of HEXPOL AB, a publicly traded company on the Swedish Stock Exchange. We are a fast-growing manufacturer of the world's highest quality polyurethane wheels, tires, and custom parts. Stellana serves various industries with our primary focus on the material handling market. Our sales and manufacturing locations are in Sweden, USA, China, Sri Lanka with a distribution center in Germany.

Great to have you here!
You are one step closer to a new possible journey, let us tell you why...

...We are looking for someone who enjoys working in a team environment and possesses professionalism, integrity, and strong communication skills. This highly visible position will offer the right candidate a unique opportunity to use their analytical and creative talents to assist in growing our global business.

The Role:
You will be working with the sales department to develop collateral, ads, social media posts, blog, targeted email campaigns and other marketing materials. An emphasis on developing insights into market conditions and directions, customer and competitor research, and data analytics to improve our web site and social interactions and drive content creation.
You will track digital analytics for the website and social media – and continue to strategize improvements as needed. You will also aid in design and implementation of business intelligence reports. Manage and execute Stellana’s website development and improvements in collaboration with sales management. This position reports directly to the Director of Global Sales and Marketing and will interface on a regular basis the with the global sales management staff and sales team to drive our marketing strategic initiatives.
To be successful you need to have excellent skills in the English language both in writing and verbal. You are comfortable and have the ability to present complex information in a clear and concise manner. Since you will be working with the different sites around the world some travel maybe required.

Essential qualifications:
University Degree in Marketing or related field.
2-3 years of combined work experience in marketing, business intelligence, analytics, or a similar business function.
Exceptional English language skills in writing and speaking, demonstrated experience generating articles and case studies with a focus on driving the strategic marketing plan forward.
Initiate and building marketing campaigns to target potential customers for each division including but no limited to social media and email marketing.
Experience with web-based applications and knowledge of website analytics.
Proficiency and experience working within the Adobe Suite – especially Photoshop, InDesign, Illustrator and Video editing skills in Premiere Pro. You will be the one creating the content and “final touches”.
Gather market intelligence information through research and analysis of various internal and external sources.
If you think that you will do great in this role, convince us. We’re open minded!
The process will have ongoing interviews and calls so don’t wait, apply today!
In this recruitment, Stellana collaborates with FSK Group AB. Responsible recruiter is Ludwig Bengtsson and if you have any questions feel free to contact me at tel: 070 873 92 43 or Ludwig@fskgroup.se
Apply as soon as possible at www.fskgroup.se
Have an amazing day!

Title: Inside Sales Representative (Internship) - POLISH Speaker
Description:
About us
S2M-group is a global agency on a mission to support industry-leading IT & Software companies with complex sales cycles to grow their business and boost revenue at scale. Our integrated demand generation services help our clients position their solutions & connect with their best prospects anywhere in the world.
When you join us, you will work amongst like-minded individuals: determined problem-solvers with a global mindset and passion for complex B2B Software Sales. We take pride in being a dynamic, global and multi-cultural crew (20+ nationalities) split between in Spain, France, Thailand, China & Canada.

What you will do
As an Inside Sales Representative (Intern), you will join a team that works to help our clients (mostly large IT software vendors) to grow their sales pipeline and brand awareness. You will use S2M-group's value-based selling methodology to research, hunt, qualify and pass leads to our clients.
Your key day-to-day tasks will include:
Understand our clients' IT solutions and target markets by analyzing business cases, finding different angles to approach prospects and researching key players, competitors, and trends.
On behalf of our client, conduct outbound campaigns using our value-based selling approach.
Engage, qualify, and convert leads through multi-channel prospecting (emails, calls, social, etc.).
Gather data & analytics to ensure reporting processes are completed.
Support direct manager in building, maintaining and managing the relationship with our clients.
Research accounts, identify key players, generate interest and develop accounts to stimulate opportunity.
Adapt to new situations quickly and think on your feet.
Maintain accurate and up to date, CRM notes on potential opportunities inside accounts.

What you need to succeed
You wish to grow in a complex B2B Software Sales environment.
You are fluent in Polish and English.
You have excellent verbal and written business communication skills.
You are an independent worker with the capability to multi-task and prioritize.
You are highly motivated and wish to thrive within Sales & Marketing and play a key role in B2B Sales processes.
Ability to work in a high-energy sales team environment, phenomenal and collaborative teammate.
1-2 years of relevant experience in marketing or sales is a plus but not necessary.

Why choose S2M-group?
International work environment with +15 nationalities.
Comprehensive hands-on training to get you on board and help you excel in your role.
Supportive team culture with horizontal hierarchy.
Team building activities.
Knowledge apprehension about the IT & Software industry worldwide.
Learning & Development monthly sessions.
Personal development plans and regular performance reviews to assure your growth career wise.
Opportunity to voice your opinion and insight on the decisions being made.
Package benefits include fixed remuneration, capped bonus, restaurant card, others.
S2M-group is an equal opportunity employer (EOE) that is committed to diversity and inclusion in the workplace. We make hiring decisions based solely on qualifications, motivation, and business needs.

Title: Product Owner Data & Analytics for Telia Finance
Description:
Product Owner Data & Analytics
Do you want to bring new insight and solutions to help improve how Telia relies on data to make decisions and take actions?
My name is Marcus Söderberg and I am leading the Telia Finance Product Team. We are a team of 20 people responsible for Telia Finance financial product portfolio for B2B and B2C customers.
We are looking for our next team member to drive the Data and Business Analytics area within our B2B domain. In this role will work collaboratively with all business areas within Telia Finance to understand, challenge and document the requirements whilst leading the delivery of successful data driven initiatives. The position is based in Telia's HQ in Solna, Stockholm!
The role
As Product Owner Data & Analytics you will play a high-profile role in driving operational transformations within the analytics field. You will work on leading innovative transformation projects connected to the field of analytics and you will be a part of defining strategies, roadmaps, backlogs and execution plans to deliver business value to improve our stakeholders’ insights and operational efficiency.
In our Product Team you will work closely with other product owners, senior business stakeholders, developers and the IT departments in translating business needs into technical requirements for the product and development teams. In this role you will manage and drive your own activities, as part of a self-organizing team, you set the tone, build tasks, and determine what needs to get done.
Is this you?
We are looking for an experienced, business driven, and analytical team player that has the capability to analyse, drive insights and present business data in an easy and structured manner to different stakeholders.
Requirements
At least 3 years of experience in the analytics field, such as developer, data analyst, business analyst or product owner similar
Experience of working with complex project and different stakeholders
Experience in visualization tools such as Business Objects, Qlik Sense, Excel, or Power BI
An understanding of the fundamentals in data modelling and data warehousing
Good communication skills in Swedish and English
Experience of working with SAFe, Confluence, and Jira is considered a plus!
It’s more than just a job
At Telia Finance, we will give you the tools and support you need to grow both professionally and personally. We can offer you your next big opportunity in a creative, motivating, and welcoming company where everyone can be themselves with equal access to opportunities. In addition to an attractive and inclusive work environment, we also enable flexibility and offer a wide variety of employee benefits.
Interested?
If you find this interesting, don’t hesitate to apply for this job. If you have any questions or just want to hear more, feel free to connect with me on LinkedIn or contact our recruiter Ebba at ebba.pers@teliacompany.com or +46 76 496 44 06. We look forward to receiving your application!
Welcome to Telia Finance – Home to your next big opportunity!

Title: Databricks Data Engineer - Malmö
Description:
Interested in belonging to the strongest Databricks community in the Nordics? Learning from experienced architects and getting access to lots of upskilling material and courses? Then we’re looking for you.
What You’ll Do
In your role as a Databricks Data Engineer you will be working with the latest tools within data ingestion, ETL and reliable orchestration for data, analytics & AI. We work with both batch and streaming data that powers analytics dashboards & productionized machine learning models.
As a Global Strategic Partner with Databricks, our close collaboration enables better projects for our clients. In our team deliveries, we can get support from Databricks to ensure quality architecture and better end result.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are also partners with other technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want!
Archicture is highly valued at Capgemini, and therefore we’ve invested a lot in educational architecture programs and communities where architects can share and develop ideas. So, if you’re interested in becoming an either a solutition architect or entreprise architecture, we have learning communities for you.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Spark, Pandas or Azure Data Factory
Experience with the Databricks Lakehouse Architecture
Good understanding of the Databricks Platform
Excellent Python skills
Excellent SQL skills
Good Spark skills
Good skills in DevOps processes with git version control and CI/CD practices
Good communications skills
Ability to work well in a team
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Databricks: Delta Live Tables
Databricks: Unity Catalog
Software Engineering
Experienced with streaming systems
Data Modelling (Data Vault, Star Schema etc)
Test Automation
Experience with setting up Azure, AWS or GCP Infrastructure
Infrastructure as Code tools such as Terraform or Biceps
Spark Query Optimization techniques

Title: Lead Data- och Analytics Arkitekt
Description:
Just nu söker jag Lead Data- och Analytics Arkitekt (BI, och Datawarehouse) till vår specialistsatsning!
Vill du få chansen bygga upp ett nytt specialistområde samt skapa förmåga inom Data och Analytics?
Vi bygger ett helt nytt specialistområde inom IT Arkitektur där människor, innovation och teknik kommer vara i fokus. Vårt fokus ligger inom 4 domäner Data, Cloud, Säkerhet och Automation.
Du kommer få vara med och skapa något nytt med örat mot rälsen kring Data trender och teknikutveckling. Du kommer få spännande uppdrag som ger dig ny kunskap och erfarenhet samtidigt som du delar din kunskap med andra och du kommer jobba i en kultur där vi vill ha roligt tillsammans.
Vårt fokus är att hjälpa kunder skapa förmåga och värde samt bli mer data drivna, ta fram lösningar samt implementera dessa.
På taktisk nivå jobbar vi med att ta fram målbilder samt realisera Data-/analytics lösningar samt leda team att exekvera och på operativ nivå utveckla lösningar gällande:
Microsoft Azure Analytics Stack inklusive Azure Data Lake
Synapse
Databricks
Data Factory
Stream Analytics
Azure Functions
PowerBI
Analysis Services
Azure SQL DB
Event Hub
IOT Hub
Vi erbjuder roliga och utmanande uppdrag, möjligheter till att utveckla sin specialistkompetens, superb kultur och roliga aktiviteter. Du är med och leder och affärsutvecklar ett specialistområde som skapar förutsättningar för en fantastiskt kul resa.
I denna roll kommer du vara i en ledande position samtidigt som du bidrar med spetskompetens inom modernisering och utveckling av molnbaserade dataplattformar. Du ansvarar för framtagning av målbild samt bästa arkitekturlösning givet kundens förutsättningar och kommer vara med på hela resan fram till implementerad lösning. I din roll kommer du vara med och bygga upp teamet och andra fantastiskt skickliga kollegor i nära samarbeten.
Dina ansvarsområden:
Skapa, designa, bygga och underhålla lösningar för att möta våra kunders affärsbehov i deras dataplattformar
Lösa komplexa problem och utveckla proof of concepts för att validera idéer och tekniker
Hålla dig uppdaterad om teknik och verktyg inom BI/DW samt Dataplattformar i molnet.
Ge teknisk vägledning till kunder och data engineers och BI-utvecklare
Agera mentor
Bygga och leverera verksamhetskritiska analysplattformar

Grundläggande kvalifikationer (krav):
Uttrycker dig väl i tal och skrift på svenska och engelska då du kommer samverka med våra kunder/kollegor nationellt och internationellt
Examen i datavetenskap, ingenjörsvetenskap, matematik eller motsvarande erfarenhet
Minst 4 års erfarenhet av datateknik, utveckling av ETL-pipelines med CI/CD, Data Quality Management och driftsfrågor
Erfarenhet av SQL, NoSQL och datamodelleringsfärdigheter
Minst 3 års erfarenhet av att bidra till arkitektur och design (arkitektur, designmönster, tillförlitlighet och skalbarhet)
Bra kunskaper i DevOps- och CI/CD-distributioner med verktyg som Azure DevOps, GitHub/GitLab, Jenkins

Önskvärda kvalifikationer:
Erfarenhet av att utveckla analytiska pipelines för big data, relationsdatabaser, NoSQL och datalagerlösningar
Praktisk erfarenhet av: Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory, Azure Functions, Synapse, Azure SQL DB, Databricks, Cosmo Db, Azure Data Factory, Data Migration Service, SSIS, etc.
Erfarenhet av att använda Big Data filformat (parquet/ delta table)
Meriterande:
Kunskap inom Spark/Cloudera/Hadoop/Hive
Erfarenhet av att utveckla tjänster på Azure/ AWS/ GCP
Programmeringserfarenhet med Java/Scala/Python med stark bas inom objektorienterad design och SOA
Certifieringar DP-200 Implementing an Azure Data Solution, DP-201 Designing an Azure Data Solution, AZ-400: Designing and Implementing Microsoft DevOps Solutions

Personliga egenskaper:
Vi söker dig kommunikativ och i ditt sätt att leda andra samt har ett coachande förhållningssätt gentemot dina kollegor.
God kommunikations och presentationsförmåga då rollen kräver att du kan presentera och visualisera data för våra kunder.
Du behöver även kunna visa på god samarbets- och kommunikationsförmåga eftersom du samverkar med både kollegor och kunder i din roll.
Slutligen behöver du vara en relationsorienterad person som trivs med att ha kontakt och skapa relationer med både kunder och kollegor.

På Softronic erbjuder vi:
Kollektivavtal
Flexibel arbetstid och arbetsmiljö med möjligheten att både arbeta hemifrån och kontor beroende på uppdrag och kund
Friskvårdsbidrag
Individanpassad kompetensutveckling samt utbildningspott för certifieringar etc
30 dagars betald semester per år
Vara med och leda affärsutveckling inom specialistområdet
Prestigelös kultur i gruppen där fokus ligger på samarbete, kunskapsdelning och utveckling.

Anställningsform:
Fastanställning
Rörlig och fast lön

Softronic fokuserar på att samla de vassaste specialisterna inom IT arkitektur, tekniskt ledarskap och utveckling till ett helt nytt spännande område.
Vill du veta mer kontakta: Vanessa Löfving, vanessa.lofving@softronic.se, 070-885 30 00.

Om Softronic
Vi på Softronic jobbar ständigt med att förﬂytta våra kunder mot morgondagens teknik. Vare sig det handlar om att utveckla AI, automatisera processer eller modernisera en äldre lösning med bibehållen tillgänglighet. En annan sida av det vi gör är att vi hjälper våra kunder att utveckla innovativa och driftsäkra tjänster som skapar samhällsnytta genom att förenkla människors liv och jobb. På så sätt blir vi och vår teknik en positiv kraft i samhället och en del i att göra världen lite mer hållbar. Det är det vi kallar GoodTech.

Vi ser arbetet och arbetsplatsen som en av flera energigivande delar i människans liv. Därför odlar vi aktivt en kultur av gemenskap och lust, där brädspelskvällar, löprundor med kollegorna längs vattnet eller en ﬁka på terrassen är viktigt och ska få lov att ta plats. Genom gemenskap och samhörighet blir det också enklare att tillsammans vidareutveckla våra förmågor, för att i förlängningen kunna vässa vårt erbjudande mot våra kunder.
Kunderna är främst medelstora och större företag och organisationer i Sverige. Softronic som grundades 1984 är börsnoterat på Stockholmsbörsen, Nasdaq OMX, och har ca 420 medarbetare i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö, Sundsvall och Arjeplog. www.softronic.se

Title: Full-Stack Developer (Intern)
Description:
Who we are
We are an early-stage startup hell-bent on improving the post-purchase experience in the e-commerce industry, starting with the biggest pain point: returns. We move fast and expect a lot because we're working on something that will truly make the e-commerce industry more sustainable, financially and environmentally. With COVID19 crisis accelerating the migration from offline to online, together with booming acquisition costs, increasing customer loyalty has become paramount. At the same time, with increasing online sales, retailers suffer from booming returns.
yayloh is a SaaS solution for e-commerce retailers, which digitalizes and automates the return process and unleashes the potential of return data. yayloh will increase customer satisfaction and loyalty while improving retailers profitability and reducing environmental impact. Using data analytics and applied machine learning, yayloh allows e-commerce retailers to understand their customers needs on an advanced level. yayloh is backed by the early-stage VC Antler. Also worth mentioning, we have happy customers and a growing pipeline in different countries!
What we’re looking for
We are looking for a full-stack developer to be involved in everything from new feature development, bug solving and releasing new versions to our production environment. You will also interact with our UI/UX team and frontend developers. This will enable you to understand everything which goes into building our saas solution.
You will also be involved in requirement gathering and interact with our customers when it comes to enhancements and bug-fixing.
Requirements
Web programming knowledge - preferably python and react.js
Understanding of how websites work end-to-end
Sql skills
Bonus Skills
Knowledge with HTML / CSS / Javascript
What we offer?
Being part of a very early stage start-up where we expect you to be independent, creative, free thinking. We are two co-founders with a strong skillset combination, with respective deep experience in retail and software development.
The dream team
We are international from day-one with a co-founding team from France and India and English is the company language so everyone feels included. Our first market is the Nordics but we dream big and are building a global company.
We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters so we don’t see failures but learning opportunities. Innovation is at the heart of everything we do and we believe anything is possible when you can think freely, without boundaries nor pre-set frameworks.
We don’t count your hours and you can work from your couch if this is where you perform the best, what we will care about is how much you contribute to make the product better!

How to apply?
Send Resume and short intro email to nikhil@yayloh.com

Title: Strategic Advisor within Data & AI
Description:
As a Strategic Advisor, you will join our team of leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers make the right decisions and give them a solid foundation to succeed on their journey towards becoming data driven. Capgemini Insights & Data is the Nordic market leader in Data & Analytics.
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data has a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
With our strong track record as the Nordic market leader in Data & Analytics, you will be able to leverage our expertise and resources to deliver high-impact solutions to our clients. With us you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of clients and industries, together with amazing colleagues.
Are you a strategic thinker with a passion for data and artificial intelligence? Do you thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment? If so, we want you to join our team as a Strategic Advisor within Data & AI! As a Strategic Advisor, you will be responsible for providing expert guidance and recommendations to our clients on how to leverage data and AI to achieve their business goals. You will work closely with our clients to understand their needs and challenges and use your strategic thinking skills to develop tailored solutions that drive results.
To be successful in this role, you will need to have a strong background in business as well as data and AI. We equally value if you come from either a solid technical background or a more business-oriented role, you thrive in the center of business and technology. You also need excellent communication and relationship-building skills. Previous experience from a consulting or advisory role is a strong advantage.
As a Strategic Advisor, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing Data & AI Solutions.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients on how to use Data & Analytics to align with the business strategy and achieve business goals.
Guiding our clients in the decision making of how to develop their data strategies to align with the business strategy.
Driving initiatives to create the foundation within data & AI.
Driving initiatives to create a data driven organization.
Working with stakeholder management, change management etc.
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Advisory, Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
More information about life at Insights & Data: https://capgemini-insights-dat...
Who You Are
What we are looking for:
You are a business-oriented person with a strong understanding on what makes organizations work and businesses tick.
You have experience on working with strategy development, objective setting, follow up etc.
You have hands on experience of developing data strategies for organizations.
Hands on experience on how to organize work within the data & analytics field for different kinds of businesses.
Familiar with data management, data security, and access control in the cloud.
People with experience from one or more business domains, for example finance, retail, industry, services, telecom, public, energy etc.
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills as well as stakeholder management.
Driven, proactive individuals who are eager to make a positive impact on our clients and our business.
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience in architecting and designing data solutions using trade-off analysis
Knowledge of different information architecture patterns
Experience on how to work with governance and master data within the data & analytics field.

Title: BI & Data Engineer - Stockholm
Description:
Veritaz is a fast-growing IT-consultant firm. Our company is made up of insanely bright people from over 4 countries, and we are located in Sweden, UK, US and Pakistan. The voyage has been incredible this far, but it is only the beginning.
Assignment Description:
We are looking for a BI & Data Engineer who is experienced in working with data management and data warehousing.
Do you value openness, transparency, and empowerment? Our squad is high performing cross-functional team who are set with a mission to provide win-win exchanges for our customers.
What you'll do:

● Cooperate with other teams within Data & Analytics, as well as with technical and business teams.
● Be part of the journey as we deliver on our company’s vision to enable the freedom to move in a personal, sustainable, and safe way.
● Continuously strive to improve current tools and methodologies to improve the analysis of information.
● Define and maintain internal processes and quality standards documentation to ensure process controls and audits are up to date and aligned to the company’s standards.
Who you are:

● Have DBA experience, or experience working with SQL server configuration or optimization and data modelling.
● Good knowledge of arete with patient data or other sensitive data where there has been a requirement to relate to security and legal space around this.
● Excellent communication, teamwork skills, inter-personal and Organizational skills.
● Experience in developing ETL pipelines in GCP using Big Query, Data flow and Data proc is an added advantage.
Job Type: Full-time
Ability to commute/relocate:

What is your salary expectations?
When will you be available to join?

Sweden (Preferred)

Title: Enterprise Data & Technology Architect
Description:
You will be responsible for defining and maintaining the target data architecture and the target technology architecture to support it (for the data & analytics domain). You will set the conceptual roadmap for how to move from the current state to the target and support and guide the initiatives required for the transition. You will do this in close collaboration with architects for other domains, the data governance function, delivery teams and business representatives.
You will have an active role in various decision forums, represent us to external partners and create a great foundation for further development. This position is more than what meets the eye. You will get the chance to push boundaries and influence your daily work. All as part of a caring and open culture where we live our values, work hard, have fun and operate with a long-term perspective.
You will be part of Ikano Bank, where we create possibilities for a better living by providing banking and financial services. We do it with different perspectives, natural curiosity and long-term focus. A unique chance for greater responsibility and future opportunities. Let’s achieve great things together.

We create solutions that simplify finance

We are looking for senior architect with good wide experience, which has a strong understanding of solutions innovation. The ideal candidate has several years of experience working as a solution architect. You have an ability to dive into various solutions while developing new solutions/services and make strong contributions in architectural discussions.
You possess strong technical and communication skills with the ability to translate technical topics to business stakeholders as well as translate business topics into technical designs and solutions. The position will report to the Chapter Lead for the Architectural team and will be based in Malmö.

Are you the one for Ikano?
Key responsibilities
Set and communicate the data architecture and data technology architecture standards and guidelines.
Utilize a reference data architecture to describe and communicate current state of data architecture
Keep an up to date view on the technology architecture for the data & analytics domain (integration, warehouses, lakes, analytical tools, etc)
Define and maintain the target data architecture and the corresponding target technology architecture, document gaps and create conceptual, value driven, roadmap to close the gaps.
Facilitate the selection of tools and packages for all components in the data & analytics landscape.
Provide support to solution architects in the implementation of initiatives along the roadmap
Represent the data & analytics domain in architecture boards and assess impact of initiatives in other domains on data & analytics.
Ensure that the architecture for new initiatives are aligned with the Enterprise Architectural roadmap and overall Ikano guidelines and target architecture
Experience
Take ownership and take pride in understanding your stakeholders and the business you support
Possess strong communication skills and can have discussions on different levels, ranging from developer to C-level.
Are structured and analytical and can conceptualize complex architectural issues
Have minimum 5 years experience working with data / data technology architecture in an enterprise context
Have experience in working with both data (big data, DWH, data management, etc) and Analytics (BI, predictive, advanced)
Several years of successful professional experience in Architecture design and implantation
Knowledge in BIAN model
Core Banking platform (e.g. Cards and Loans) and Origination systems is an added advantage
Fluent in English – spoken and written!
Ability to work in a team and within Ikano’s values
Knowledge on Monitoring, Vulnerability Scanning and Patch Management & Deployment (added advantage)

Join us now – together we will find a better way
Let’s achieve great things together. Send your application before 31st January 2023

About us
Ikano Bank creates possibilities for better living by offering simple, fair and affordable services, enabling a healthy economy for the many people. Our offer includes savings and loan products for consumers, sales support services for retailers, and leasing and factoring solutions for businesses. We conduct business in Sweden, Denmark, Finland, Norway, the UK, Poland, Germany and Austria. Ikano Bank is a part of the Ikano Group, an international group of companies active within banking, real estate, production, insurance, data analytics and retail, who owns 51 % of the Bank. Ingka Group, a strategic partner in the IKEA franchise system, operating 378 IKEA stores in 31 countries, owns the remaining 49 % of Ikano Bank. Ikano Bank’s head office is located in Malmö, Sweden and the company is registered in Älmhult, Sweden where the business was once founded. Our mission is to simplify the many people’s lives so they can focus on living it. We do this by working together to create simple and meaningful solutions based on fair terms that bring value to our customers.
Find out more about us on www.ikanogroup.com

Title: Trainee - Verksamhetsutvecklare digitalisering av transportsystemet
Description:
Om jobbet
Under tolv månader deltar du i ett omfattande traineeprogram som främjar din personliga utveckling, breddar ditt kontaktnät och ger dig kunskap om våra olika verksamheter. Du rustas i förändrings- och projektledning och tillsammans med övriga traineer deltar du i utvecklingsuppdrag utifrån olika case för att lära och påverka. Du förväntas att själv ta initiativ, etablera kontakter och planera en stor del av ditt traineeår. Som exempel kan du välja att göra studiebesök eller kortare praktikperioder inom de verksamheter som intresserar dig. Det erbjuds möjlighet till samverkan med andra myndigheter och externa aktörer i Sverige och internationellt. I arbetet ingår resor, både nationellt och regionalt.
Vi på avdelning Transportkvalitet ser fram emot att välkomna dig som trainee! Vår avdelning ansvarar för expertstöd och analyser inom tillgänglighet för personer och gods, trafiksäkerhet, miljö, hälsa samt klimat. Huvuduppdraget är att fånga in omvärldens krav och behov samt samverka med samhällets aktörer för att bidra till att de transportpolitiska målen nås. Vårt motto är att vara en expertavdelning i världsklass där vår kunskap gör skillnad. Vår avdelning tar, genom forskning tillsammans med andra aktörer, fram ny kunskap. Vi har omfattande samarbete på EU-nivå och stöttar regeringen inom avdelningens kompetensområden. Som trainee är du med i hela avdelningens verksamhet och du kommer bland annat att:
genomföra analyser och utredningar, bedriva omvärldsbevakning, benchmarking och föreslå utvecklingsinsatser
delta i verksamhetsområdets datadrivna analyslab där vi genomför avancerade analyser inom avdelningens expertområden
stödja verksamheten i projekt- och förändringsledning när nya initiativ ska implementeras, detta görs genom insatser för att utveckla den digitala transportinfrastrukturen
medverka i utvecklingsarbete av analytiska metoder, verktyg och tillgång till data samt kommunicera val av metod och resultat
delta i EU-arbete i projekt samt vara expertstöd inom digitaliseringsområdet
Jag som blir din chef heter Petter Åsman. Jag är chef för Enheten Gods & ITS, en av avdelningen Transportkvalitets åtta enheter. Vi är en nationell expertenhet inom gods och logistik samt intelligenta transportsystem (ITS). På enheten är vi idag 14 medarbetare som stöttar Trafikverket med expertstöd inom våra områden. Såhär beskriver en av våra medarbetare som tidigare varit trainee den traineeåret:
"Det är ett roligt, utvecklande jobb, med många nya utmaningar. Som trainee får du en unik möjlighet att jobba över verksamhetsområdena och få en insikt i hela Trafikverkets verksamhet, vilket är till stor nytta efter traineetiden", säger Jonna som började som trainee på enheten och idag arbetar som utredare med inriktning ITS och digitalisering.
Kvalifikationer
För att trivas som trainee behöver du ha ett stort intresse för att utveckla transportsystemet kombinerat med ett digitaliseringsintresse och förståelse för digital omställning samt en vilja att medverka till att skapa innovation. Arbetet innebär många kontakter både inom och utanför Trafikverket och förutsätter att du som person är duktig på att skapa goda relationer, kommunicera och förmedla budskap på ett enkelt sätt anpassat till mottagaren. Du drivs av att arbeta i en föränderlig miljö och jobbar självständigt, ser vad som behöver göras och agerar därefter. Du har en stark egen drivkraft och besitter en mycket god problemlösningsförmåga som gör att du identifierar problem och utvecklar lösningar ur ett helhetsperspektiv.
Vi söker dig som
har civilingenjörs- eller masterexamen inom samhällsbyggnad, transport, fordon, information eller industriell ekonomi
har mycket goda kunskaper i svenska i tal och skrift
Det är meriterande med kurser eller examensarbete inom Data Science/AI, Big data analytics, visualisering av data, business intelligence, statistik i dataanalys eller innovation/innovationsledning.
Din akademiska examen ska ha uttagits under 2021, 2022, alternativt kommer du att ta din examen senast september 2023.
Övrig information
Vi använder främst mail (från mejladress: noreply@heroma.se) för att göra utskick och kallelser. Kolla din inkorg och även skräppost/SPAM regelbundet under denna tid för att vara säker på att du får all information från oss! I denna rekrytering används webbaserade tester som en del i urvalet.
När du ansöker ska du inte bifoga något personligt brev. Istället för att bifoga personligt brev, får du möjlighet i ansökningsformuläret att beskriva varför du är intresserad av den här tjänsten. Detta är en tillsvidaretjänst som inleds med en provanställning på 6 månader. Tillträde till tjänsten är den 1 september 2023.
De första intervjuerna är planerade att hållas den 6-9 mars 2023 via Skype.
#LI-AB2
Ansökan
De frågor som du får besvara när du skickar in din ansökan kommer att ligga till grund för det första urvalet vi gör.
Som sökande till Trafikverket kan du eventuellt behöva gå igenom en säkerhetsprövning. Den innehåller säkerhetsprövningssamtal och registerkontroll innan anställning, om tjänsten är placerad i säkerhetsklass. I vissa fall krävs svenskt medborgarskap för säkerhetsklassade tjänster.
På Planering skapar vi innovativa lösningar som bidrar till att nå de transportpolitiska målen, såsom klimatmålen och nollvisionen. Vi planerar Sveriges statliga infrastruktur för väg och järnväg samt långsiktigt även för sjö- och luftfart. Hos oss arbetar du nära den politiska arenan och våra samarbetspartners - men framförallt nära medborgare och näringsliv.
På Trafikverket jobbar vi med att göra Sverige närmare. Vi tror på att en förening av olika erfarenheter, bakgrunder och perspektiv är den bästa grunden för att bygga en arbetsplats fri från diskriminering och en miljö där alla trivs och gör sitt bästa. Vi tror på mångfald där den gemensamma nämnaren är pålitlighet, engagemang och mod. För det är så vi bäst representerar vårt samhälle.

Title: Data Engineer inom Analytics/Business Intelligence
Description:
Slutdatum för platsannonsering/sista ansökningsdatum:
2023-02-28
Om företaget / verksamheten
Drivs du av att utveckla analytics-lösningar och att omvandla data till affärsmöjligheter? Som data engineer i LKAB kommer du att arbeta i en toppmodern dataplattform, som baseras på ETL/ELT-verktyg, data warehouse och system för datahantering.
Avdelningen Digitalisering och Koncern IT består idag av cirka 90 IT-förmågor. Vi söker nu någon som kan förstärka vår grupp Data & Analytics, som har sin huvudfokus på drift, förvaltning och utveckling av lösningar inom beslutsstöd.
Om tjänsten
Som data engineer kommer du att arbeta i LKAB:s dataplattform, som baseras på Wherescape som automations- och ELT-verktyg och Snowflake som datalager. Dataplattformen är en viktig del i LKAB:s data- och analyslandskap och du kommer ha stora möjligheter att påverka och driva utvecklingen av plattformen.
I arbetet kommer du delta i att designa, modellera och utveckla rapporterings- och analyslösningar som hjälper LKAB:s organisation med bättre beslutsstöd, för att bättre se, förstå och agera utifrån sin data.
Du kommer även ingå i vårt analytics-team där du i samarbete med BI-utvecklare, representanter från verksamheter och data scientists säkerställa att data är upptäckbart, tillgängligt och av rätt kvalitet.
Dina arbetsuppgifter består av att samla in data från källor, tillsammans med verksamheten säkerställa att data är av hög kvalitet och designa lösningar som möjliggör analys.
De viktigaste uppgifterna är:
Utifrån verksamhetens behov designa och skapa stjärnscheman i datalagret
Samarbeta med Power BI-utvecklare i teamet för att säkerställa att datamodellerna är optimerade för analys
Skapa förutsättningar för AI, ML och data science
Bidra med idéer kring arbetssätt kopplat till dataplattformen
Att driva ständiga förbättringar inom området är en självklar del i arbetet.
Dina kvalifikationer
Vi söker dig som ha en IT-utbildning på högskolenivå eller motsvarande arbetslivserfarenhet. Du har erfarenhet av SQL, ETL/ELT-utveckling, datamodellering och data warehousing.
Som person bör du ha en god kommunikationsförmåga som du kan anpassa till alla typer av intressenter och du ska ha goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska såväl i tal som skrift. Du behöver vara konsultmässig och ha lätt för att få förtroende från verksamhet, kollegor och leverantörer.
Det är meriterande om du har erfarenhet av:
Wherescape, Informatica eller Snowflake
Bygga data pipelines med hjälp av Python
Versionshantering och CI/CD
Erfarenhet av verktyg och plattformar inom datahantering, som exempelvis Informatica.
B-körkort och gymnasial examen är ett krav för alla tjänster inom LKAB.
Övrig information
För mer information om tjänsten, vänligen kontakta gruppchef Daniel Nordvall, 072-707 67 01 alt.
daniel.nordvall@lkab.com
eller sektionschef Anna Wester 070-298 18 15 alt.
anna.wester@lkab.com
.
För mer information om rekryteringsprocessen, vänligen kontakta HR koordinator Hanna Gustafsson,
Hanna.Gustafsson@lkab.com
.

Kiruna/Svappavaara
Sakari Alanko, Unionen, 0980-725 08
Malmberget/Luleå
Unionen Södra - Per Ola Eriksson, 0920-38076
SACO-klubben Södra - Annika Taavoniku, 0970-79532
Ledarna Södra – Annica Kaati 0970-76765
Vi erbjuder
Vår unika verksamhet kräver anställda med unik kunskap. Oavsett tjänst hjälper och stöttar vi varandra – över avdelnings- och organisationsgränser – inom hela koncernen. Det är viktigt för oss att du vill bidra till den varma och inkluderande kultur som ligger till grund för vår framgång. Vi drivs alla av ett starkt engagemang och vill skapa värde för våra kunder. Vi gillar utmaningar och välkomnar nya idéer. Vi bygger förtroende genom att ta ansvar och hos oss kommer alltid säkerheten först. Våra värderingar är alltså engagemang, innovation och ansvar. Förutom att bli en del av vår breda organisation med gott om möjligheter till utbildning och utveckling i ditt dagliga arbete erbjuder vi alla medarbetare ett attraktivt utbud av förmåner.

Title: Azure Data Engineer - Malmö
Description:
As an Azure Data Engineer you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards data-driven decision-making. We are all passionate about data!
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are partners with different providers of technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Azure Data Factory
Experience in Data Lake or Lakehouse Architecture
Excellent SQL syntax skills
Information- and Data Warehouse modeling
Good skills in code versioning such as GIT GitHub, DevOps
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience from platform modernization
Experience from Tabular cubes and DAX
Databricks
Snowflake
Experience in Snowpro, Matillion or DBT
Data vault modeling
Agile work process

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
We are looking for a Data Engineer to join our Data & Analytics team at Volvo Car Mobility. With your help we can gain new key insights into how we can replace car ownership and contribute to helping more people move freely, meaningfully and sustainably.
The Data & Analytics team has a crucial role in setting Volvo On Demand's data-driven agenda and is responsible for the full data strategy; ranging from finding actionable insights to building data pipelines to designing machine learning-based data products. You will contribute to and learn from this talented team of data professionals in a caring, collaborative, fast-paced and exciting environment.
Our Technology
Our data platform, as well as our backend, is fully built in the cloud using Google Cloud Platform. We ingest data into our BigQuery data warehouse using Pubsub and Kubernetes-based service. Using dbt we create structured and modeled data consumable for analytical as well as data product use-cases. Visualization and analysis is done through Tableau and notebooks. We are also building a few machine learning models using Python and an MLOps-approach.
Your engagement here will include but won't be limited to:
In your role, you will work on exposing relevant data to track large and small features. Your contributions will span across the whole data stack; ranging from pure data engineering work, such as building event-based data-ingestion services, to analytics engineering where you design datasets for analysis and machine learning. You will participate in creating a scalable data platform, work with marketing and product analytics tools as well as productionize and deploy machine learning models.
As a Data Engineer, you will work closely with the product and engineering organization, representing the data perspective in a product domain and ensuring data plays an integral role in product development. Supported by experienced Data Engineers, Data Scientists and Data Analysts in the Data & Analytics team, you will work in a cross-functional and educational way. This enables you to gain insight and expertise in product development, software engineering and analytics; a combination of competencies we believe will shape you into a great Data Engineer as you grow your role and responsibilities over time.
You show experience with most of the following…
Developing data processing pipelines
Designing data models
Knowledge of software engineering fundamentals, e.g. CI/CD, testing etc.
Knowledge of an OOP-programming language as well as SQL
You are curious, eager to learn, conscientious and kind
A couple of years of experience working in a data or software engineering role
You studied Data Science, Engineering or another quantitative field such as Physics, Statistics or Mathematics
Extra awesome if you...
Experienced different data architecture paradigms, e.g. Data Lake, Data Warehouse, Data mesh
Developed machine learning models and/or deployed models using MLOps best practices
We offer a wide range of benefits designed to enhance your working life at Volvo On Demand:
Pension & compensation. You'll be looked after with Collective Agreement and ITP pensions.
Learning & innovation. Involving lunch & learns and a generous annual education budget.
Tools & equipment. From laptop to phone and more, you'll get the gear you need to do your best work.
Discounts & offers. On driving with Volvo On Demand and Hertz as well as for eating and shopping at MOOD.
Health & wellbeing. Including a 5 000 SEK annual allowance to spend, and private health insurance.
Parental support. Plenty of leave lets you take time off for what's most important.
At Volvo Car Mobility, we believe that a diverse and equal working environment is essential for the well-being and development of our co-workers. We strive for a well-balanced representation of gender and ethnic identities at every level of the organization. In this way, we hope to create an open-minded, smart, and enjoyable workplace.
Does this sound interesting to you? Then we are looking forward to your application in English!
If you have any questions, you are welcome to email us at careers@m.co. Note that due to GDPR, we do not accept applications via email.

Title: Senior Corporate Investigator
Description:
About this opportunity
The Corporate & Government Investigations team is responsible for conducting internal investigations of possible violations of the Ericsson Code of Business Ethics and handling government-facing investigations. This position reports to Head of CGI Hub Europe and can be located in different locations in Europe.

You will
Conduct internal investigations on a variety of topics, including allegations of fraud, corruption and regulatory breaches, as well as potential violations of Ericsson’s Code of Business Ethics
Develop scope and investigation strategy to execute best in class investigations
Gather and review evidence and other forensic reviews
Conduct witness interviews
Draft clear, well-written reports summarizing investigation reports
Present investigation findings to senior leaders in meetings like Remediation Committees.
Assist in government-facing investigations, including preserving and collecting relevant data, producing data to authorities, and tracking materials provided
Assist in reporting about investigations to Ericsson’s Monitor and the U.S. Department of Justice
Assist in the development of investigations processes and policies
Coordinate with key functions such as Compliance Office, Internal Audit, Group Security and Group Functions e.g., Finance and People Function.
Interact with key persons in our Business Units and Market Areas
Act with integrity, objectivity and fairness
Manage multiple matters at once in a fast-paced environment
You will bring
10 years’ experience in investigations or related areas
Experience from forensic review and search
Experience from data analytics
Demonstrated superb communication skills, both verbal and written
Demonstrated ability to handle and manage complex matters
Fluency in English
Additional Requirements
Experience working on complex financial investigations, such as anti-corruption, anti-money laundering, and accounting fraud
Experience working for a government agency
Experience working with a company under a compliance monitorship
Experience at a multi-national company or working with multi-national clients
Other language skills
Why join Ericsson?
At Ericsson, you´ll have an outstanding opportunity. The chance to use your skills and imagination to push the boundaries of what´s possible. To build never seen before solutions to some of the world’s toughest problems. You´ll be challenged, but you won’t be alone. You´ll be joining a team of diverse innovators, all driven to go beyond the status quo to craft what comes next.

What happens once you apply?
Click Here to find out more about what our typical hiring process looks like.
Vetting including references and relevant background screening will be conducted for final candidates.

Application
Last day to apply is 5th of February, 2022.
We look forward to receiving your application in English. Please note we cannot accept applications via email.
For specific questions please contact recruiter Mirosław Coś at miroslaw.cos@ericsson.com

We welcome the opportunity to meet you!

Encouraging a diverse and inclusive organization is core to our values at Ericsson, that's why we nurture it in everything we do. We truly believe that by collaborating with people with different experiences we drive innovation, which is essential for our future growth. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and realize their full potential as part of our Ericsson team.
Ericsson is proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer, learn more.
