Title: Trainee - Verksamhetsutvecklare digitalisering av transportsystemet
Description:
Om jobbet
Under tolv månader deltar du i ett omfattande traineeprogram som främjar din personliga utveckling, breddar ditt kontaktnät och ger dig kunskap om våra olika verksamheter. Du rustas i förändrings- och projektledning och tillsammans med övriga traineer deltar du i utvecklingsuppdrag utifrån olika case för att lära och påverka. Du förväntas att själv ta initiativ, etablera kontakter och planera en stor del av ditt traineeår. Som exempel kan du välja att göra studiebesök eller kortare praktikperioder inom de verksamheter som intresserar dig. Det erbjuds möjlighet till samverkan med andra myndigheter och externa aktörer i Sverige och internationellt. I arbetet ingår resor, både nationellt och regionalt.
Vi på avdelning Transportkvalitet ser fram emot att välkomna dig som trainee! Vår avdelning ansvarar för expertstöd och analyser inom tillgänglighet för personer och gods, trafiksäkerhet, miljö, hälsa samt klimat. Huvuduppdraget är att fånga in omvärldens krav och behov samt samverka med samhällets aktörer för att bidra till att de transportpolitiska målen nås. Vårt motto är att vara en expertavdelning i världsklass där vår kunskap gör skillnad. Vår avdelning tar, genom forskning tillsammans med andra aktörer, fram ny kunskap. Vi har omfattande samarbete på EU-nivå och stöttar regeringen inom avdelningens kompetensområden. Som trainee är du med i hela avdelningens verksamhet och du kommer bland annat att:
genomföra analyser och utredningar, bedriva omvärldsbevakning, benchmarking och föreslå utvecklingsinsatser
delta i verksamhetsområdets datadrivna analyslab där vi genomför avancerade analyser inom avdelningens expertområden
stödja verksamheten i projekt- och förändringsledning när nya initiativ ska implementeras, detta görs genom insatser för att utveckla den digitala transportinfrastrukturen
medverka i utvecklingsarbete av analytiska metoder, verktyg och tillgång till data samt kommunicera val av metod och resultat
delta i EU-arbete i projekt samt vara expertstöd inom digitaliseringsområdet
Jag som blir din chef heter Petter Åsman. Jag är chef för Enheten Gods & ITS, en av avdelningen Transportkvalitets åtta enheter. Vi är en nationell expertenhet inom gods och logistik samt intelligenta transportsystem (ITS). På enheten är vi idag 14 medarbetare som stöttar Trafikverket med expertstöd inom våra områden. Såhär beskriver en av våra medarbetare som tidigare varit trainee den traineeåret:
"Det är ett roligt, utvecklande jobb, med många nya utmaningar. Som trainee får du en unik möjlighet att jobba över verksamhetsområdena och få en insikt i hela Trafikverkets verksamhet, vilket är till stor nytta efter traineetiden", säger Jonna som började som trainee på enheten och idag arbetar som utredare med inriktning ITS och digitalisering.
Kvalifikationer
För att trivas som trainee behöver du ha ett stort intresse för att utveckla transportsystemet kombinerat med ett digitaliseringsintresse och förståelse för digital omställning samt en vilja att medverka till att skapa innovation. Arbetet innebär många kontakter både inom och utanför Trafikverket och förutsätter att du som person är duktig på att skapa goda relationer, kommunicera och förmedla budskap på ett enkelt sätt anpassat till mottagaren. Du drivs av att arbeta i en föränderlig miljö och jobbar självständigt, ser vad som behöver göras och agerar därefter. Du har en stark egen drivkraft och besitter en mycket god problemlösningsförmåga som gör att du identifierar problem och utvecklar lösningar ur ett helhetsperspektiv.
Vi söker dig som
har civilingenjörs- eller masterexamen inom samhällsbyggnad, transport, fordon, information eller industriell ekonomi
har mycket goda kunskaper i svenska i tal och skrift
Det är meriterande med kurser eller examensarbete inom Data Science/AI, Big data analytics, visualisering av data, business intelligence, statistik i dataanalys eller innovation/innovationsledning.
Din akademiska examen ska ha uttagits under 2021, 2022, alternativt kommer du att ta din examen senast september 2023.
Övrig information
Vi använder främst mail (från mejladress: noreply@heroma.se) för att göra utskick och kallelser. Kolla din inkorg och även skräppost/SPAM regelbundet under denna tid för att vara säker på att du får all information från oss! I denna rekrytering används webbaserade tester som en del i urvalet.
När du ansöker ska du inte bifoga något personligt brev. Istället för att bifoga personligt brev, får du möjlighet i ansökningsformuläret att beskriva varför du är intresserad av den här tjänsten. Detta är en tillsvidaretjänst som inleds med en provanställning på 6 månader. Tillträde till tjänsten är den 1 september 2023.
De första intervjuerna är planerade att hållas den 6-9 mars 2023 via Skype.
#LI-AB2
Ansökan
De frågor som du får besvara när du skickar in din ansökan kommer att ligga till grund för det första urvalet vi gör.
Som sökande till Trafikverket kan du eventuellt behöva gå igenom en säkerhetsprövning. Den innehåller säkerhetsprövningssamtal och registerkontroll innan anställning, om tjänsten är placerad i säkerhetsklass. I vissa fall krävs svenskt medborgarskap för säkerhetsklassade tjänster.
På Planering skapar vi innovativa lösningar som bidrar till att nå de transportpolitiska målen, såsom klimatmålen och nollvisionen. Vi planerar Sveriges statliga infrastruktur för väg och järnväg samt långsiktigt även för sjö- och luftfart. Hos oss arbetar du nära den politiska arenan och våra samarbetspartners - men framförallt nära medborgare och näringsliv.
På Trafikverket jobbar vi med att göra Sverige närmare. Vi tror på att en förening av olika erfarenheter, bakgrunder och perspektiv är den bästa grunden för att bygga en arbetsplats fri från diskriminering och en miljö där alla trivs och gör sitt bästa. Vi tror på mångfald där den gemensamma nämnaren är pålitlighet, engagemang och mod. För det är så vi bäst representerar vårt samhälle.

Do you want to be part of something new and exciting, where innovative thinking and bold ideas are taking our Rock Tools Services into the next era? At Sandvik Mining and Rock Solutions (SMR), we’re proud of our brilliant minds who are working together and creating innovations that our customers only thought they could dream about.
Intrigued? Check out our exciting world!

To get a glimpse of the world you’ll be joining, look at this YouTube-video about our concept “You’ll never work alone”. ”Sustainability is a key driver for the future of our planet; if the global community fail to act- humanity will face unprecedented challenges in the short-, mid- and long-term.”- Jens Holmberg, President Rock Tools Division, Sandvik Mining and Rock Solutions

Title: Data Center Production Operations Manager
Description:
Meta is seeking a forward thinking experienced individual to join the Data Center Operations Team. The person should enjoy working in a fast-paced environment where adaptability and flexibility is key to their success. We seek an IT professional with management and leadership experience and advanced hands-on technical skills in Server Hardware, Project Management, Quality Management, Data Analytics, Networks, OS repair, Linux and Automation (ideally in a data center environment). Having depth and breadth of knowledge of managing servers in a large-scale distributed environment is a core competency of this individual.The Production Operations Manager is responsible for managing and maintaining server production including uptime, utilization, systemic technical issues and repairs throughout the Data Center.


Data Center Production Operations Manager Responsibilities:
Managing a Data Center Operations Team accountable for the maintenance and operation of server hardware and supporting infrastructure at scale
Accountable for the health of server capacity delivering Meta's products and services from the data center site, and for ensuring operational delivery through collaboration and partnership with peer organizations
Work with peer organizations and regional teams that affect and deliver services to data center operations such as network operations, project management, facilities/maintenance management, logistics, hardware design, automated tooling and supply chain operations in order to successfully maintain data center uptime to enable ongoing business growth
Mentoring and developing engineers and technicians such that they can run daily operations with minimal supervision
Lead a diverse, world-class data center operations team, developing both the technical capabilities and leadership qualities of engineers and technicians
Collaborating with other Production Operations Managers in data center sites around the globe to evolve and optimize processes and approaches in a globally consistent way to allow Meta to scale and grow effectively
Creating and driving a culture of ownership, innovation, collaboration, accountability, and safety. Support and contribute thought leadership to the development and implementation of business practices, process and automated tooling which enables the growth and ongoing management of our global data center IT footprint
Manage server upgrades, integration, automated OS provisioning process, rebuilds and other projects as required. Understand and debug network, hardware, and Linux OS related issues
Identify and participate in the creation of documentation for the global DC knowledge base. Implement process improvements and inform best practices in data center operations
Predicting data center growth and scaling issues before they occur and implement solutions
Drive specifications for tooling and automation that facilitate deployment, monitoring, automated remediation and decommissioning of server hardware at scale



Minimum Qualifications:
BS or BA in technical field or commensurate experience
4+ years experience managing 5+ technical resources
Knowledge with Linux and hardware systems support in an Internet operations environment
Familiarity with Python, SQL and/or shell scripting knowledge
2+ years experience managing multiple projects within the same time schedule
Solid knowledge of enterprise level infrastructure
Understanding of out-of-band/lights-out server communication methods, such as IPMI and serial console
Proven time and project management skills
Experience training, mentoring, and leading other engineers and technicians
Knowledge and ownership of a hyper-scale computing fleet through the use of data trending and analysis to identify trends and systemic issues, reporting out globally



Preferred Qualifications:
4+ years of experience in large-scale data center hardware deployments and building scalable infrastructure

Title: Marketing Specialist
Description:
About Us
Tre Kronor Media was founded in Sweden 2007 and Denmark 2013 as a new kind of media agency with 100% focus on our customers’ business results, and ROI.
Today we are a One-stop-shop, a 360-service agency within data, adtech, crm, media, insight, and strategy. We are a personal business partner driven by our curiosity for our customers’ operations, and our passion for the media. With our expertise in both traditional and new media, we create value for our clients.
We have been awarded Media Agency of the Year in 2009, 2010, 2011, 2013, 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018 and 2019. We are also certified as a Great Place to Work 2018, 2019 and 2020. Our partnership with Making Science strengthens our service offer by adding a full range of digital capabilities. And through our global media agency partners, you’ll reach new channels across the globe.

We are growing rapidly, and we are now looking for the next teammate to our Marketing and Communication team. Do you want to become part of our driven family?
Some details about your department
Marketing and Communication is a challenging and international department at Making Science, with the ability to represent and unite our entire digital family through our actions. Our objective is to position the Making Science brand at the highest level, both nationally and internationally, and using our know-how and expertise to become trailblazers in our area. At our department, each day is a new adventure, and we face it with a lot of enthusiasm. We are motivated by our drive to continue learning, new challenges, innovation in processes, growth as a team, and helping the company expand through our work. We do great things that make every Making Science employee feel proud, and contribute to positioning the company higher and higher empowering our values.
What we’d like you to do:
Overseeing and developing marketing campaigns
Conducting research and analyzing data to identify and define audiences
Devising and presenting ideas and strategies
Managing campaigns on social media
Paid and organic targeting
Promotional activities
Compiling and distributing financial and statistical information
Writing and proofreading creative copies
Maintaining websites and looking at data analytics
Organizing events and product exhibitions
Updating databases and using a customer relationship management (CRM) system
Coordinating internal marketing and an organization’s culture
Monitoring performance
Propose and keep within a budget for the country
What we’d like you to bring:
You have a Bachelor's Degree in Marketing / Advertising / Business
You have between 2 and 3 years of professional experience in a similar role
Digital industry knowledge
PR experience
You possess great communication skills and are capable of building valuable relationships with different stakeholders
You know and enjoy working with a team
You are capable of adapting to a fast-paced environment
You have a strong attention to detail
You possess good organization and planning skills
You are creative and enjoy writing
You have commercial awareness
You have good numerical and IT skills
Good command of English Language (other languages like Danish, Norwegian or German are a plus)
Perks of joining us
Office centrally located in the middle of the city in Stockholm
Great participation and the opportunity to be involved and influence your daily work
Good community spirit and great closeness between management and employees
We think that a balance between work, leisure and personal development is important
Health benefits
Market pension terms and private pension advice via our partner Max Matthiessen
You will never stop learning with us: trainings, learning capsules, an e-learning platform, and many more
Be a part of a young, adventurous, and professional team, with people you’ll grow fond of
Marketing Specialist
Stockholm Marketing & Communication

Title: Lead Software Engineer, Data Analytics
Description:
With 950 employees, over $250M in sales, 1,500+ clients, and rapid year-over-year growth, Recorded Future is the world's most advanced, and largest, intelligence company!
We are looking for an outstanding software engineer with a strong interest in data analytics to join Recorded Future's Analytics Team within the R&D organization. You will be joining a group of talented engineers, linguists and data scientists that share a common interest in solving challenging data analytics tasks in large distributed systems with rich data. The team's responsibilities include core parts of the analytics pipeline such as data harvesting, natural language processing, structured data analytics, predictive analysis, etc. We strive to make our data as actionable and comprehensive as possible and have fun.
You would get the chance to develop great software in a fast-moving environment close to our global clients and their needs. Together, we'll improve our product to meet increasing demands while focusing on scalability and quality. You will also get a chance to experiment with new technology and explore what solutions are most suitable for solving real-world problems. You would join a dynamic team eager to take on new challenges and are passionate about what they do.
What you will be doing as a lead software engineer:
Work on complex issues where analysis of situations or data requires an in-depth evaluation
Work together with our product teams to understand and deliver expected results
Continuously design, develop and deploy our software, analytics, and processing technology to support new and existing features with a focus on high availability, excellent quality, low latency, and scalability
Select methods and techniques for obtaining solutions
Determine methods and procedures for new assignments, may coordinate efforts of colleagues
Measure and evaluate features and system metrics to continuously improve data quality and service performance
Support DevOps and MLOps activities
Access to the energy, velocity, and freedom of an entrepreneurial culture
Networks with key contacts outside area of expertise
Proactive, go beyond expectations, and independent
Having wide-ranging experience uses professional concepts and company objectives to resolve complex issues creatively and effectively
What you will need as a lead software engineer:
Minimum 10 years of experience as a software engineer
Experience with data analytics and data processing
Experience in technical leadership, leading project teams, and setting technical direction
Experience with more than one general-purpose programming language (Scala, Java, Python)
Ability to learn other coding languages as needed
Experience and comfort in API development
Architect and develop solutions to ambiguous problems with significant impact
Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to effectively advocate technical solutions to product, engineering, and business audiences
Bachelor's and/or Master's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or equivalent education/work experience
Strong English skills are a must
Bonus points for:
Experience in RabbitMQ, MongoDB, Elasticsearch, Docker, AWS, and Software libraries for Machine Learning like TensorFlow, Spacy, etc.
Experience in ML Ops, deploying and monitoring real-time inference models and ETL (extract, transform and load) pipelines
Experience from a DevOps role
Experience handling both research and development
Deep understanding of machine learning and image/video/text/patterns processing algorithms
Experience in building, deploying, and improving Machine Learning models and algorithms in real-world products
Diversity has been essential to Recorded Future since day one, and that is clearly visible in all teams in the company, yet there's always room for improvement. In essence, we welcome applications that will help us improve this even more.
Why should you join Recorded Future?
Recorded Future employees (or "Futurists"), represent over 40 nationalities and embody our core values of having high standards, practicing inclusion, and acting ethically. Our dedication to empowering clients with intelligence to disrupt adversaries has earned us a 4.7-star user rating from Gartner and 8 of the top 10 Fortune 100 companies as clients.
Want more info?
Blog & Podcast: Learn everything you want to know (and maybe some things you'd rather not know) about the world of cyber threat intelligence
Instagram & Twitter: What's happening at Recorded Future
The Record: The Record is a cybersecurity news publication that explores the untold stories in this rapidly changing field
Timeline: History of Recorded Future
Recognition: Check out our awards and announcements
We are committed to maintaining an environment that attracts and retains talent from a diverse range of experiences, backgrounds and lifestyles. By ensuring all feel included and respected for being unique and bringing their whole selves to work, Recorded Future is made a better place every day.

If you need any accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to our recruiting team at careers@recordedfuture.com

Recorded Future is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply. Recorded Future does not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, gender including pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, marital status, veteran status, disability or any other characteristic protected by law.

Recorded Future will not discharge, discipline or in any other manner discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because such employee or applicant has inquired about, discussed, or disclosed the compensation of the employee or applicant or another employee or applicant.

Title: Head of Digital Marketing (fixed term)
Description:
Welcome to your new job where you empower people to live circularly by shaping Sellpy's digital marketing across all channels and markets.
As Head of Digital you will be key in driving Sellpy’s growth through developing our paid acquisition across all markets and digital channels and lead our digital team.
You will be part of Sellpy’s commercial team and report to the Chief Commercial Officer. You will work closely with the regional marketing teams, creative team as well as data & analytics. This role is a temporary role (maternity cover) from April/May 2023 to approx end of Feb 2024 but if Sellpy and you are a great match we are positive that we can find an exciting role within the digital team or another team within Sellpy afterwards.
In short, you will:
Develop our paid acquisition channels across all our markets
Lead a team of four digital marketers and designer
Be in charge of budget allocations for all paid channels together with the heads of each sales region and steer according to CAC targets
Develop our tracking and analytics including our attribution and LTV models
Work closely together with our Creative team and Region Heads to develop our marketing campaigns and request marketing assets as well as execute campaigns and always-on-marketing content
Manage the strategy, setup, bidding, measurement and optimization of our paid campaigns and channels
Conduct uplift studies and optimize our channel and funnel strategy accordingly
Stay up to date with developments and new techniques in digital marketing and implement new and creative digital growth strategies
You need:
5+ years of experience in performance marketing with a strong track record
Hands-on experience of building campaigns within Google and paid social channels (esp. Meta, YouTube, Snapchat, Pinterest and TikTok)
Data-driven decision mentality and sound business judgment through strong analytical thinking
Great communication skills in English, Swedish is a plus
Experience in e-commerce
Proficiency in Excel or Google Sheets
We are impressed if you have:
Leadership experience
A relevant degree in engineering, business, economics or similar
Worked in Funnel
Worked in SQL
You get to:
Develop Sellpy’s paid acquisition to empower more people across Europe to live circular
Develop your team and work closely with talented colleagues across all multiple markets
Enjoy a flexible WFH policy and get more time for what’s important
Relax with 30 days of paid vacation
Use staff discounts at Sellpy and the H&M brands
Thrive in a very social and driven people culture!
About Sellpy
Sellpy’s vision is to empower everyone to live a circular life. We believe there is huge financial, social and environmental value in prolonging the life of things and clothes. We are proud to be the leading service for second hand items, and one of the fastest-growing scale-ups in Sweden. The list of countries we are available in grows by the day. Since launching, we have given new life to more than 20 million pre-owned items, saving almost 100.000 tons of CO₂.
Location
You are welcome to do all these things at our new office at Medborgarplatsen in Stockholm, our office in Friedrichshain Berlin or from home. We want you to enjoy a flexible work setup because well, it’s 2023 and digital meetings work just as fine!
Form of employment: Full-time. It is a temporary contract (maternity cover) until the end of February 2024. But if Sellpy and you are a great match we are positive that we will have an exciting role and be able to extend the contract afterwards.
Start: April or beginning of May 2023

Title: Tax Data Analyst
Description:
Nasdaq is now looking for a Tax/Transfer Pricing Data Technology Analyst to join the global Tax team. In this role, you will work mainly with Transfer Pricing, being involved in implementing and improving data processes and technology related to Transfer Pricing and Tax within Nasdaq.
The position is located in Stockholm, Sweden.
Nasdaq has business operations in over 30 countries, and we expand our business through organic growth and acquisitions worldwide. Being part of the international Tax team means you will work closely with colleagues in Stockholm, New York, Bangalore and Sydney as well as with the Business and Accounting teams.
About Nasdaq
Nasdaq is a leading global provider of trading, clearing, exchange technology, listing, information and public company services across six continents. Our technology powers more than 90 marketplaces in 50 countries.
Here, you will work for a global tech leader committed to breaking down barriers to inclusive prosperity. We see technology as a way to allow people to work together more productively and effectively by centralizing data, analytics, and market intelligence.
We’re committed to building a more diverse and inclusive workforce. Not only is it our responsibility to do better, but we also need representative voices to power the fresh thinking that is vital for our business and our clients.
Role and Responsibilities
To be successful in this position, you must have an interest in data, processes and technology and like to translate that in to the exciting world of transfer pricing. We hope you are keen to analyze our tax data! You will be involved in identifying opportunities to improve processes related to tax/accounting information.
You Will Bring
Bachelor of Science degree in business administration, accounting, computer science, data science or equivalent
2-5 years of professional experience within transfer pricing, tax or financial accounting from an international organization
Expertise in Microsoft Office Products, excellent skills in Microsoft Excel
You should be an analytical and ambitious person, who can work independently
Good communication skills in written and spoken English
Would be great if you have
Proficiency with any of the accounting systems, Workday Financials or Hyperion Essbase (SmartView)
Some experience with data transformation tools such as Power BI, Alteryx
Some experience with operational tax/transfer pricing technology products such as Longview
Does This Sound Like You?
We offer a full-time position located in Stockholm, Sweden. As we will start reviewing resumes February 1st, please submit your application in English as soon as possible.
At Nasdaq, we provide our employees with the resources and opportunities they need to chart a career of achievement along with a strong compensation package that includes annual bonus opportunity, equity grants, as well as an employee stock purchase program. Nasdaq Sweden provides its employees 32 days of annual vacation (plus 1 additional flex day every two months), health insurance, career development programs, and more. We advocate flexible ways of working and have a hybrid work model.
Come as You Are
Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

Title: Data Protection Officer
Description:
At Epidemic Sound we are reinventing the music industry. Our carefully curated catalog, with over 35,000 tracks, is tailored for storytellers, streaming services, and in-store soundtracks. Countless clients around the world, from broadcasters, production companies, DSPs, and YouTubers rely on our tracks to help them tell their stories. Epidemic Sound’s music is heard in hundreds of millions of online videos daily, across millions of playlist streams, and in thousands of in-store locations. Headquartered in Stockholm, we’re spread across offices in New York City, Los Angeles, Seoul, Hamburg, and Amsterdam. We’re growing fast, have lots of fun, and are taking the music industry with us.
We are searching for a Data Protection Officer to champion data protection culture and compliance at Epidemic Sound. You will form a key part of the Operational Compliance team and have the opportunity to work closely with the entire organization, both strategically and operationally. You will monitor our data practices and ensure compliance with applicable privacy laws and regulations with support from data protection specialists in the legal department and compliance managers. Although we are a global company, this position will be based in our Stockholm office.
Your key responsibilities will include:
Monitoring compliance and conducting internal audits within the framework of applicable laws and regulation (such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)).
Together with other teams and internal stakeholders maintaining, creating and implementing practices around data protection and security.
Developing and conducting awareness raising activities, delivered to all levels of technical & legal proficiency.
Researching and keeping up to date on new requirements from a regulatory and compliance point of view.
Act as the main point of contact in relation to supervisory authorities.
We believe that the ideal candidate is/has:
2 to 5 years experience of working with data protection matters, ideally with experience from data analytics or as a DPO (or similar role) in a tech company with focus on analytical data processing.
Integrity with excellent communication and stakeholder management skills - not afraid to speak up, combined with great ability to listen and give pragmatic, actionable advice.
A solid understanding of the cybersecurity and IT industry (you will be working closely with security engineers and will need to understand basic security concepts).
Fluent in English, written and oral.
Curious to learn more about who we are and what we do? Check out our brand new "About us" page https://www.epidemicsound.com/about-us/
We have lots of fun soundtracking the world and our annual Spring Bash is an event that captures this perfectly. Take a look at our most recent one, a virtual celebration!
*
Application*
Do you want to be a part of our fantastic team? Please apply, in English, by clicking the link below.
We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business and a better world. We value diversity and encourage everyone to come and soundtrack the world with us.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Paradox puts the player in focus and we need Data Analysts to do that. Do you want to join us on our journey?
We are looking for a Data Analyst to join the Data, Analytics & BI department. As a member of the Analytics team you will work closely with the product/marketing teams to help them become truly data-driven. You will also support high impact business decisions by analyzing external and internal data and producing reports and visualizations.
On a day-to-day basis you will work with our digital marketing teams and support them with insights based on quantitative data generated by our users. You’ll function as the data specialist, proactively working with stakeholders to support business decisions and evangelizing a data-driven culture at Paradox.

Some of your key responsibilities are:
Function as a specialist to our digital marketing teams, promoting data-driven development in our digital channels (web, email).
Interprets and analyzes data using exploratory mathematic and statistical techniques based on the scientific method.
Responsible for tracking, reporting, and analyzing the performance of marketing activities, ad-hoc analytic requests, and development of dashboards in Tableau/GA.
Design and interpret results of A/B tests to continuously improve conversion and retention.

To be able to do a good job we expect the following from you
Experience working with business, digital or marketing analytics.
M.Sc. or other higher education in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science or similar.
Experience of using web analytics tools, SQL as well as R/Python.

We will consider the following as a plus
Experience from the gaming industry or with digital products
A great passion and interest in gaming and Paradox games in particular.

If you think that this description matches your background, we highly encourage you to apply as soon as possible as we will interview candidates continuously for this position. In your application, please show us why your previous experiences and skills would work for this role and why you are interested in working at Paradox.
Since we strive for a diverse workplace, we highly encourage anyone, no matter who you are, to apply for this job if you think that you'd be able to come into this position if you think you’d be a great fit."

Title: Product Manager
Description:
Working at NA-KD is unlike any other fashion gig. We’re a young company with a start-up mentality and (a borderline insane) hunger to be the best. In less than 5 years NA-KD has become one of the fastest growing fashion e- com brands in the world. And we have a 4 million strong community to prove it. How? We see no limitations, only possibilities. No failures, only learning opportunities. We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters. We’re doers. And if you dream of going to work every day to build the next big thing – then welcome home.
We are passionate about sustainability so we aim to use lower- impact materials for our products to save the environment.
We have an open position for:
Product Manager for Acquisition and User Management Squad
WHO YOU ARE
You have 2+ years of experience as a Product Manager//Owner
You have shipped products that have delivered meaningful business results.(must have)
Experience in retail / consumer / e-commerce companies and products (must have)
Experience working in startu- ps (must have)
Proven track record in taking on end-to-end ownership of web & mobile products and successfully delivering results in a high-growth and dynamic business environment
Experience in A/B testing and data analytics to inform product roadmap
Solid technology understanding; ability to communicate effectively with Engineering and Product Design
Solid technology understanding; ability to communicate effectively with Engineering and Product Design
Experience managing multiple stakeholders from senior positions and their competing needs
You are experienced with agile (e.g. scrum, kanban) and cross-functional squads
Fluent in English, both written and spoken

WHAT YOU'LL DO
Accountable for shaping and managing roadmaps for a portfolio of digital/mobile products from strategic planning to tactical activities, based on inputs from a variety of sources and stakeholders
Engagement with business stakeholders to cover the strategic aspects of product development, including product vision definition, roadmap creation, business case creation, and follow-up
Have a data-driven approach to decision-making and prioritization and work with OKRs
Responsible for the successful end-to-end delivery of new digital/mobile products or enhancements
Involved with User Acceptance Testing and responsible for cursory production validation of digital products following a release
You will work with various stakeholders across the whole organization, including senior management, tech, marketing and brand.

WHY YOU WILL ENJOY WORKING WITH US
start-up working envirounment
global environment
personal and professional development
a number of voluntary benefits
freedom to add value/make a difference
Location: The position may be fully Hybrid based in NA-KD's offices in Gothenburg or remotely in Sweden.
Apply now or get in touch by sending your CV to: email: iryna.gnatyshyn@na-kd.com

Title: Campaign Manager
Description:
Furthermore, you have a keen interest in the industry and are always on the look-out for new Talents, emerging trends and opportunities.
This is a permanent position with a 6-month probation period based in Stockholm. Starting date: March 2023 or earliest possible date.
Main tasks and responsibilities
Responsible for securing the implementation of signed campaign deals for our Talents.
Responsible for structuring, developing and optimizing the business together with Talent Manager and Head of Operations.
Time planning and scheduling of campaigns for Talents including coordination of all parts of each collaboration for Talents.
Ongoing monitoring and final reporting to clients after completed campaigns including data analysis.
Assist Talent Manager and Head of Operations with quotations and budget work.
Create necessary routines, templates and internal/external presentations for meetings.
Responsible for invoicing of the campaigns.
Ongoing close dialogues with Talents for strategic advice and development.
Provide Patriksson Talent's own digital channels with updated material and content.
Serve as an exceptional ambassador for Patriksson Talent and network with key stakeholders in the industry.
External monitoring of talents, collaborations and campaigns.

Relevant postgraduate or professional degree.
Specific Talent representation experience is a bonus.
Excellent coordination, project management and administrative skills.
A true team player with strong ability to also work independently.

Society www.incsociety.com.

Title: Service Engineer
Description:
Job Title
Service Engineer
Job Description
We’re looking for a multiskilled and passionate Service Engineer to join our team in Sweden.
Working for Signify means being creative and adaptive. Our culture of continuous learning and commitment to diversity and inclusion creates an environment that allows you to build your skills and career. Together, we’re transforming our industry.
As the world leader in lighting, we’re constantly ahead of the curve. Through our leadership in connected lighting and the Internet of Things, we’re breaking new grounds in data analytics, AI, and smart homes, offices, cities and more!
Signify is one of the few companies in the world to achieve carbon neutrality and our next sustainability goals are even bolder: doubling our positive impact on the environment and society by 2025.

See
#SignifyLife
through the eyes of our employees!
As a Service Engineer you'll be responsible for servicing and supporting Signify customers to the highest levels of customer satisfaction.
We’re on the lookout for forward-thinking innovators with a passion for technology, problem solving and customer service. If you have experience within the technical service industry and as a person is outgoing with a can-do attitude and a customer first mindset, get in touch!
What you’ll do
Technical problem diagnostics, root-cause determination, and incident resolution
Installed base maintenance services, measures, and validations etc.
Onsite or remote customer support and service
System commissioning and optimization
System- and service design validation
Perform customer training session remotely or in classroom
Facilitate customer feedback to internal stakeholders
Presale customer advisory and guidance
Technical customer advisory participating in customer meetings, events, trade-fairs etc.
What you´ll need
Technical degree e.g., in electrical engineering, IT or other relevant education
Proactively engage with customers face-to-face, by phone or in writing
Experience within servicing networked building- or industry automation systems or similar (e.g. BMS, HVAC, CTS, PLC etc.)
Operational skills and knowhow within TCP/IP networking incl. wireless, NOS (e.g.Cisco IOS), Server and Database Systems (e.g. MS Server and SQL), Cloud- and API interfaces etc.
Fluent language skill in English
What you’ll get in return…
The Nordics has one of the highest engagement scores in Signify globally and we are on a growth journey, so you will join a fully engaged team with positive and skilled colleagues and a one-of-a-kind culture
We offer multiple opportunities for your career development (e.g. mentoring, coaching and stretch assignments) with strong international exposure for dynamic profiles. Learning is fundamental to our culture. Through continuous learning we are transforming the industry. You have the chance to learn every day, acquire new skills and perspectives through customized online programs and on-the-job experiences
What we promise
We’re committed to the continuous development of our employees, using our learning to shape the future of light and create a sustainable future. Join the undisputed leader in the lighting industry and be part of our diverse global team. #WeAreSignify #SignifyLife
Any and all information you share with us as part of your application procedure will be assessed during the application process. Please be informed that unless our vacancy explicitly references a third party recruitment agency, Signify does not engage with third-party agencies. Applications should be made directly to our career site.
Our process
Did we spark your interest? Then apply through our Signify career site. After a pre-selection process based on your CV, you will be invited for a video interview and after successful review, a business interview.

Title: Software Engineer - Physical Meeting Points – Store, Group Digital
Description:
Software Engineer - Physical Meeting Points – Store, Group Digital




WHO WE ARE

At IKEA we have a vision to help more of the many people to have an affordable and better everyday life at home and be more convenient to where they are. At the same time, we aspire to become truly people and planet positive.

We believe that you, like us, thrive when meeting incredible people that are on the same mission at IKEA. People that are very humble, supportive and absolutely committed to leading home-furnishing retail into the future and creating a better life for more of the many people, by putting the customer at the heart of all we do.

Our team is focusing on providing digital tools for our amazing coworkers in our physical stores worldwide. We listen to our coworkers, make data driven decisions and we always have the customer in mind. We dare to try and learn new things. We are now looking for engineers that share our passion.




WHY WE WILL LOVE YOU

At IKEA, you’re welcome no matter where you come from, what you believe, and what you look like. We don’t even care how you have furnished your home. We’re interested in you simply because you’re you. Our different views, backgrounds, and personalities make us better understand our customers, give us more fun at work and spark more and better ideas. Perhaps your unique take on something could lead to a great idea that creates a better everyday life for many people.

We are looking for a passionate engineer who is excited about technology and innovative ways of working and wants to be a part of shaping the future of IKEA!

To be successful in this role we believe that you have experience in building cloud-based services with Node and Typescript. You enjoy DevOps way of working with CI/CD, IaC and observability. You have a genuine drive to solve problems and create value for our customers. You enjoy working in an agile team taking ownership of the full product lifecycle. As a person you have a curious nature, learn quickly, and contribute to solving problems across the tech stack.

You get energized by delivering high quality code in a cloud environment, always eager to improve processes and explore new technology opportunities. You see simplicity, ownership, and accountability as key elements for a collaborative and empowered team.




A DAY IN THE LIFE WITH US

We build PWAs for mobile devices. We work with a DevOps mindset, in cross functional product teams. We always focus on delivering value and doing this often with small incremental releases. We listen to feedback, measure with data and continuously improve.

You will be part of the development of backend services, cloud architecture, test automation and CI/CD. There are also opportunities for front end work depending on your interest. Part of our work is also prototyping new ideas, both individually and across teams (we love prototyping and MVP!). We value sharing sessions and pair programming for learning. And having a lot of fun!

Your skills and interests include most of the below:

Professional experience in Cloud architecture and services

Professional experience in Node, Typescript

Use to work with CI/CD, DevOps, Infrastructure as Code and GitHub

Agile mindset, being a key part of an autonomous, cross functional agile team

We work in an environment that encourages your personal growth where learning is a key factor.



OUR TEAM WITHIN IKEA

Our team is in the Physical meeting points domain where we focus on digitalize coworker operational tasks in the stores. We love to work closely and have a positive impact on our coworkers worldwide in their daily life on the store.

We are a product team with all capabilities in the team – engineering, product, design and data analytics. The foundation in the team is trust and openness. We try new things, learn, and grow together. We collaborate, pair programme and have regular social events to make sure we have fun together. Great teams build great products.

This role is based in Malmö, Sweden.




QUESTIONS AND SUPPORT? LET'S CONNECT!

Studies show that members of underrepresented communities don’t apply for jobs unless they’re 100% “qualified”. If this is part of the reason you hesitate to apply, we would like you to reconsider and give it a chance. Maybe your profile fits our needs much better than you think. We look forward to receiving your application.

From: “Why Women Don’t Apply for Jobs Unless They’re 100% Qualified” by Tara Sophia Mohr, August 2014”

If you have any questions about the position, please reach out to hiring manager Niklas Lööw at niklas.loow@ingka.ikea.com

If you have any questions about the recruitment process, please reach out to Batool Malik at batool.malik@ingka.com. Please note that we will be interviewing continuously.

We warmly welcome your application!

We’re the ones who make it possible for people to have a smarter life at home and a hassle-free and rewarding shopping experience. Together we work to find new digital solutions for every business need to help make IKEA a great and efficient place to work. We like to think of ourselves as innovative and modern, and we believe that nothing would actually work without us.

Title: Är du vår nästa Verksamhets- eller Applikationskonsult?
Description:
Vill du arbeta med erfarna konsulter på ett företag med 100 % fokus på Microsofts ekosystem? Brinner du för att skapa band med nya människor, har lätt för att kommunicera och vill bidra till att göra världen bättre genom innovation? Då är jobbet som Verksamhetskonsult eller Applikationskonsult hos oss någonting för dig!

Innofactor som företag
Innofactor drivs av att modernisera och digitalisera våra kunders organisationer. Vårt ramverk för den moderna digitala organisationen har lösningar för hur våra kunder når sina kunder digitalt, hur den nya moderna affären drivs, hur en modern arbetsplats realiseras, hur tjänster säkert flyttas upp i molnet och hur företaget kan dra nytta av ett datadrivet tillvägagångssätt. Vi fokuserar uteslutande på Microsofts ekosystem och våra nordiska experter arbetar i framkant av digital transformation med innovation och implementation av både små och storskaliga lösningar. Vi drivs av att lösa utmaningar och tänja våra gränser, varje dag. På Innofactor kan du utvecklas genom intressanta projekt och genom vårt nordiska nätverk där vi delar passionen för att skapa innovativa lösningar för våra kunder.
Om rollen
Som Verksamhetskonsult & Applikationskonsult har du en central roll i vår organisation. Du kommer att tillhöra affärsområdet Dynamics där vi jobbar med den senaste tekniken. Du kommer vara en naturlig del av presales arbetet och hålla i workshops och demo. Du kommer vara delaktig i kravspecificering där du analyserar kundens behov samt processer och tillsammans med kollegor ta fram innovativa lösningsförslag till kunden. I implementeringsfasen står du för konfigurering low code utveckling.

Du kommer att arbeta i ett härligt team bestående av projektledare, arkitekter, utvecklare och säljare med olika bakgrund och kompetens. Du har ett tydligt kundfokus och förmågan att bygga långsiktiga relationer med kund. Du har ett genuint intresse för kundens verksamhet och brinner för att skapa innovativa och hållbara lösningar. Du besitter kompetens inom Microsoft Dynamics 365, det är ett plus om du har fördjupat dig inom Field Service, Customer Service och Power Plattform.


Du ansvarar bland annat för att:
Digitalisera våra kunders arbetsprocesser
Hålla workshops och demo för kunder
Analysera kundens nuvarande verksamhetsprocesser och behov för att hjälpa våra kunder att hitta rätt lösning
Ta fram lösningsförslag/design tillsammans med arkitekt
Konfigurering och anpassning av lösning utifrån kundens specifika krav
Agera rådgivande till verksamheten i samband med förändringsprojekt
Vara delaktig i vidareutveckling och innovation av våra erbjudanden
Om dig
Du är en person som känner dig bekväm i att beskriva dig själv som positiv, engagerad och driven. Du trivs att arbeta i team och med varierande uppgifter. Du har ett brinnande intresse för IT som verktyg, för verksamhetsförbättringar och den kundnytta du kan generera. Du har koll på den senaste tekniken och trender och håller dig uppdaterad med vad som händer inom ditt specialistområde. Du är ödmjuk och ser vikten i att dela med dig av din kompetens och erfarenhet. Du gillar att jobba verksamhetsnära och drivs av förändringsarbete och kundnytta.
Med dig och ditt engagemang levererar vi nya värdeskapande resultat till våra kunder, varje dag! Ett pragmatiskt och kreativt tillvägagångssätt tillsammans med att vara engagerad och lyhörd är nyckelfaktorer för att lyckas som konsult hos oss.

Erfarenhet och kompetens
Erfarenhet av att arbeta som Verksamhetskonsult eller Applikationskonsult
Praktisk erfarenhet av Microsoft Dynamics 365 eller liknande system
Plus om du har fördjupade kunskaper inom Dynamics Field Service och Customer Service
Teknisk utbildning (Systemvetare, Data, Ekonom & IT eller motsvarande)
Meriterande
Arbetat med IT-relaterade innovationsprojekt
Vana att leda workshops och demo
Engagerad i Microsoft Dynamics communities
Förändringsledning

Vi erbjuder
Innofactor har det bredaste erbjudandet i Microsofts ekosystem med expertkunskap hos 500 anställda i Norden. I Sverige är vi 100 erfarna och engagerade kollegor som arbetar med intressanta och utmanande projekt inom Microsoft Dynamics 365, Office 365, Microsoft Power Platform, Microsoft Data & Analytics platform och Azure. Vi är en Microsoft Gold Partner i 15 kategorier och har fått utmärkelsen Microsoft Dynamics Partner, vilket vi är väldigt stolta över.
Vi jobbar tillsammans, hjälper och utmanar varandra och har roligt på vägen. Tillsammans bildar vi ett starkt team för att möta marknadens krav på innovativa och avancerade verksamhetslösningar. Vårt huvudsakliga uppdrag är att ge både organisationer och individer chansen att göra en skillnad i den digitala världen. Våra kunder befinner sig mitt i sin digitalisering och har ett stort intresse av förändring i form att förbättra och effektivisera sina arbetssätt. På så vis gör vi som konsulter/företag stor skillnad ute hos våra kunder. Arbetsmiljön är kreativ och dynamisk och det är viktigt att du som anställd får en bra balans mellan arbete och privatliv. Vi har våra lokaler på Drottninggatan mitt i centrala Stockholm.

Placeringsort: Har kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Sundsvall men söker även dig som önskar arbeta på distans.
Omfattning: Tillsvidare, heltid

Title: Team Lead - Analytics & Data Science
Description:
Why Avaus?
We are the leading marketing and sales transformation partner in the Nordics! We are 120 colleagues located at our offices in Helsinki, Stockholm, Munich, Milan and Gdansk. As a company, we have more than 15 years of experience in data-driven marketing and sales in large organizations across B2C & B2B industries.

Our vision is to become the leading actionable marketing data-asset provider in Europe by 2025. We believe that to survive, companies need to invest heavily in capabilities related to intelligence & AI, customer experience, personalisation and change management. Our mission is to foster customer-centric organizations equipped to grow and face the future. Our own future growth is heavily driven by activating data and analytics for our clients.

The Team
The Analytics team at Avaus consists of data scientists, BI & CRM analysts, and is a team of highly skilled and ambitious people, eager to improve our clients’ results by providing them with better decisions and actions based on data. We work in a wide range of tools and languages to orchestrate and automate the activation of customer data. We are a social crew and enjoy working closely together and learning from one another.

The role
As the Team Lead for our Analytics team, you will be responsible for managing team development plans, coach and guide team members and assist our operations matching the right person for projects. You will also be responsible for the team's career development, recruitment, resourcing and establishing a culture in line with Avaus cultural cornerstones. As a team lead you will need to be a trusted role model for your team and among your peers. Apart from leading your team, you’re also expected to act as a subject-matter expert in client projects. You will most likely be doing some of these things also:

People & team management
Performance reviews and dito assessments, including salary reviews
Coaching of individuals and teams
Personal & career development plans and execution
Competence area customer delivery and subject matter expertise
Team building
Operations & resourcing
Contribute to sales cases within competence area
1-1:s and individual follow-up
Participate in building a growth mindset and culture within the organization
Thought-leadership around the selected topic, both internally and externally
Who are you?
For this role, we are primarily looking for someone with strong leadership skills. It’s preferable if you have experience within marketing automation, CRM Marketing, Content automation and consulting in general. The role will also include supporting client projects and helping clients define and execute on personalization strategies.

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree within a relevant field
Multiple years of relevant work experience, preferably within consulting
Consultancy mindset and the ability to work in fast paced environments
Proven track record within people and team leadership
Extensive experience in data, analytics and reporting
Fluent in Swedish, as our customers require us to communicate in Swedish
Fluent in English
Practical information
This is a permanent position with a 6 months’ probation period, based at our Stockholm office at Katarinavägen 17. Starting date as soon as possible or by agreement. We offer a hybrid remote workplace and you will report to Head of Delivery.

Already feel like one of us? Send your applications in English as soon as possible, but no later than 2023-02-28. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Paola Banegas, Head of Talant. Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Master Data Management (MDM) konsult - Stockholm
Description:
Till flera nya projekt under hösten söker vi nu erfarna konsulter inom MDM – Master Data management. För dessa spännande projekt behöver vi stärka upp vårt MDM-team med både utvecklare, projektledare och Business Analysts.
Hos oss arbetar några av Nordens främsta experter inom Data, Analytics & AI, vilket ger oss bästa möjliga förutsättningar att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas på sin resa mot ett datadrivet beslutsfattande.
Vi bistår våra uppdragsgivare med datadriven affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling hela vägen från strategiska vägval till implementerad lösning och realiserad nytta.
Inom Insights & Data är vi ett stort team med specialister och våra tjänster spänner över områden såsom – rådgivning, framtagning av digitala strategier och roadmaps, design och implementation av AI-, IoT-, Analytics- och Data Management-lösningar. Givetvis understött av molnarkitektur och cybersäkerhet. Vår CFO Office-funktion bidrar även med expertis inom finansiell planering, budgetering och prognos samt finansiell konsolidering och koncernrapportering.
Efterfrågad erfarenhet:
Vi söker nu dig som har flera års erfarenhet inom området MDM – Master Data Management i roller som utvecklare, projektledare och/eller Business Analyst. Du har erfarenhet ifrån ett antal olika MDM projekt och du är van att arbeta med kunder i olika branscher och inom olika funktioner.
Vi ser gärna att du har erfarenhet av att arbeta med olika MDM verktyg, där minst ett av dom är Profisee eller Informatica. Vi tror även att du har lång erfarenhet av att arbeta med SQL.
Det är viktigt att du är analytisk, lösningsorienterad och nyfiken, att du har en god samarbetsförmåga samt lätt för att kommunicera. Du har relevant högskoleutbildning och du kan svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift.
Hos oss är medarbetarnas utrymme att utvecklas stort och kulturen präglas av frihet under ansvar. För dig som lockas av att vara med i Sveriges vassaste team inom Data, Analytics och AI, är detta ett jobb med framtidsmöjligheter för dig.

Title: Stena Group IT Graduate Program
Description:
Stena is so much more than one of the largest ferry operators in the world - and Stena Group IT is far from just another IT organization. We play a vital part in transforming this company by enabling all our business areas to drive digitalization in each of their respective industries. With Care, Innovation and Performance as guiding principles, our 200 colleagues at Stena Group IT are part of 16 000 Stena AB employees around the world. We are devoted to creating value for our customers within a range of different business areas - Ferry Operations, Offshore Drilling, Shipping, Property, Finance, and other business acquisitions.

Work with Stena’s multiple diverse industries!
By joining Stena Group IT’s Graduate Program, you will play a part in the digitalization of multiple organizations across Stena AB. We handle business technology solutions that put us on route to becoming the world’s first cognitive ferry company, we fine-tune data and shape IoT technology that makes buildings and tenants interact, and we support underground waste management as an innovative solution needed for a sustainable future.

The Program
During 16 challenging months, you will experience and get a full understanding of how Stena drives digitalization throughout our industries. You will work with the business units, management teams, and our five functions within Stena Group IT:
Enabling operational excellence of IT delivery through strong infrastructure platforms and ensuring everyone gets help and support through our support functions in the Shared Infrastructure and Support Services team
Procuring, maintaining, and developing solutions to enhance organizational efficiency and collaboration in the Workplace and Productivity Solutions team
Working with the Strategic Roadmap and Governance, including IT Security, Sourcing, and Ways of Working in the CIO Office team
Enabling digital business development and delivery of complex IT-projects in the Business Engagement and Project Management team
Developing and maintaining Business Applications, Business Intelligence, IoT, and Integrations in the Business Solutions team

While working in these different teams, you will continuously learn and strengthen your skillset through our development program.

Our Graduates have the possibility to shape their future careers and work in multiple areas such as Software Development, Business Intelligence, Data Analytics, Service Management, IT Security, DevOps, Infrastructure and more, while building an understanding of how our different industries operate. We love to see our employees grow and have all the possibilities to provide them with a challenging and developing career within the Stena Group.

Sail our course?
We are looking for ambitious students with a degree in Information Technology, Computer Engineering, Information Systems or equivalent, while also:
Having a passion for technology and a desire to learn and acquire new skills
Possessing a pragmatic approach to problem solving
Thriving in an entrepreneurial environment with quick decision-making
Having strong interpersonal skills and being an outstanding team-player
Being fluent in English

We look forward to fast forwarding your career in IT – and we promise that you will have fun while doing it!

For questions: itgraduate@stena.com
Submit your application today, the recruitment is ongoing! Final application date is 15th of February 2023.

Title: Engineering Manager - Data Science Platform
Description:
We are looking for an experienced Engineering Manager to join Northvolt's Data Platform within the Digitalization department. You will join and lead the team that designs, builds, and operates the Data Platform supporting Battery Cell Factory Operations.
Our factories produce large amounts of heterogenous data that get uploaded to our cloud platform, and are then processed, organized, and ready for analysis. You will partner cross-functionally with the Engineering, Production and Quality teams in the factories to drive data-driven manufacturing operations. We strive to use technology and data to co-develop solutions that matter, and welcome applicants from diverse experience levels and backgrounds.
We are searching for someone passionate about building diverse, inclusive and highly effective teams. The ideal candidate is a curious life-long learner who takes ownership and is eager to collaborate to build better products. This role is a vital member of the Ett Digitalization team is key to Northvolt's mission to enable the future of energy.
Our Connected Factory architecture is described in the AWS/Northvolt blog post https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/industries/northvolts-next-gen-connected-factory-a-digital-blueprint-factory-built-from-scratch/
We presented our vision and progress at AWS re:Invent 2022 (Northvolt part starts at 32:14) AWS re:Invent 2022 - How innovators are driving more sustainable manufacturing (SUS312)
Key responsibilities include
Lead a full-sized Data Team (7-10 people) of Data Engineers, Data Analytics Engineers, and Data Scientists through hiring, coaching, mentoring, feedback and hands-on career development
Drive and be accountable for technical delivery and work with your team on strategy, roadmap and execution
You'll work with others to shape how Northvolt’s data ecosystem works — you'll help develop our technical practices, recruiting and onboarding strategy, planning and prioritization process, and more.
Advocate operational excellence and advance high-quality development practices
Grow a healthy, collaborative engineering culture in line with the company values
Be an active part of the leadership team and collaborate with other leaders in the organization
Grow the technical expertise of the team
Apply with CV and cover letter or your complete LinkedIn profile.
Full-time employment, fixed salary.
Location: Stockholm, Sweden.
Travel: Skellefteå 2-3 days/week, 2 weeks/month during the first 6 months.
Skills & Requirements
Preferred Experience
Communication, communication, communication. You communicate fluently and humbly with all types of different humans choosing effective methods based on context, audience and purpose
Proven track record of hiring, developing and growing people. You’re committed to building diverse and inclusive teams; you value empathetic and direct communication and foster environments that are at once collaborative, empowering, supportive, and challenging—ones where people do their best work
Engineering in technical data role (Data Engineering, Data Science, Machine Learning) including processing, storage, quality, and management on GCP or AWS
Working with a diverse set of stakeholders and helping them understand the trade-offs to different product and technical decisions
Not Required (bonus points)
[Bonus] You've experienced the challenges of scaling and re-architecting data platforms and infrastructure through orders of magnitude of growth
[Bonus] Experience hands-on designing and building highly scalable and reliable data architecture using Kinesis, Lambda, dbt, Parquet, Protobuf, Airflow, Redshift or equivalent stack
[Bonus] Engineering foundation understanding (electro/mechanical/chemical/physical), preferably within the energy domain
[Bonus] Experience from fast-growing start-ups or scale-ups
[Bonus] Experience from large (manufacturing) enterprises with heterogeneous and distributed data across many domains
Skills
Excellent English written and oral communication skills
Independent, organized and entrepreneurial
Passionate team collaborator that can thrive in a diverse international environment (110+ nationalities and counting)
Qualities that we value are flexibility, sense of quality, friendliness, motivation to take on new challenges, grit and a sense of humor
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment
Fast paced & entrepreneurial culture
Warrant program
Wellness grant

Title: Director Consulting
Description:
Description
Director, IT Strategy Consulting, Digital Talent and Organisation
About the role:
Gartner’s Consulting business is an extension of Gartner’s industry-leading IT Research. From CIOs, to leaders in business and government, we help Gartner clients across enterprises translate insights into transformational actions and achieve their mission-critical priorities. Leveraging the breadth of Gartner’s resources, Consulting is growing rapidly, with unlimited potential to continue expanding our client base.
Technology Strategy Consulting. We help the C-suite make the right decisions based on how technology can transform their businesses. In today’s world, a consulting firm that is “born digital”, (with the ability to directly leverage the full power of Gartner’s research and insights) has relevance to the most important strategic decisions any business will make.
We deliver value to clients in areas such as IT Strategy Consulting, Benchmarking, Analytics and Optimization. Typically, this helps Gartner’s clients to execute on their strategic priorities, across all sectors, including:
Digital and IT Strategy
Digital, Talent and Organization
Market Gowth
Data & Analytics
What you’ll do:
Our Consulting Directors are responsible for high-level project delivery and oversight along with client relationship management. You will manage teams and advise clients at the highest strategic level on both big-picture and tactical matters, focusing on how technology enables a wide range of business outcomes.

What you’ll need:
Experience within a well-regarded management consultancy in a project delivery and sales capacity
Prior experience in a problem-solving capacity such as a solution/technical architect or analyst preferred
Experience working with multiple IT solutions
Experience working with solutions related to IT Operating Models, Future of Workforce, Digital Talent and Organizational Change
A consistent track record of leading people and building high-performing teams that leverage technology to drive the mission-critical priorities of commercial or government entities
An ability to inspire and motivate professionals from both technical and non-technical backgrounds towards a common goal
An unwavering commitment to the success of your team, and willingness to provide constructive/ corrective action when needed
Demonstrated intellectual curiosity and the creative development of solutions and strategies to solve client problems. Must adapt Gartner frameworks and methodologies to strike at the heart of a client’s most pressing business challenges
An ability to be hands-on and to manage multiple client priorities simultaneously
MBA or other advanced degree preferred
Comfortable selling to, influencing and building trust-based, value-added relationships with senior executives
Coachable and embracing of best practices and feedback as a means of continuous improvement
A consistently high achiever marked by perseverance, humility and a positive outlook in the face of challenges
Track record in achieving / exceeding revenue targets preferred
#LI-JL2
Who are we?
Gartner delivers actionable, objective insight to executives and their teams. Our expert guidance and tools enable faster, smarter decisions and stronger performance on an organization’s most critical priorities. We’ve grown exponentially since our founding in 1979 and we're proud to have nearly 16,000 associates globally that support our 14,000+ clients in more than 100 countries.
What makes Gartner a great place to work?
Our teams are composed of individuals from different geographies, cultures, religions, ethnicities, races, genders, sexual orientations, abilities and generations. We believe that a variety of experiences makes us stronger—as individuals, as communities and as an organization. That’s why we're recognized worldwide as a great place to work year after year. We've been recognized by Fortune as one of the World’s Most Admired Companies, named a Best Place to Work for LGBTQ Equality by the Human Rights Campaign Corporate Equality Index and a Best Place to Work for Disability Inclusion by the Disability Equality Index. Looking for a place to turn your big ideas into reality? Join #LifeAtGartner

Our people are our most valuable asset, so we invest in them from Day 1. When you join our team, you’ll have access to a vast array of benefits to help you live your life well. These resources are designed to support your physical, financial and emotional well-being. We encourage continued personal and professional growth through ongoing learning and development opportunities. Our employee resource groups, charity match and volunteer programs keep you connected to your internal Gartner community and causes that matter to you.
