Title: Service Engineer
Description:
Req ID:409154

What if you could participate in the strategic decisions of a leading mobility company?

Leading societies to a low carbon future, Alstom develops and markets mobility solutions that provide the sustainable foundations for the future of transportation. Our product portfolio ranges from high-speed trains, metros, monorail, trams and e-buses to integrated systems, customised services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility solutions. Joining us means joining a caring, responsible, and innovative company where 75,000 people lead the way to greener and smarter mobility, worldwide.

Join us as a Service Engineer in Gothenburg, Sweden and you will be looking at a career-defining role.

Your mission?

As a Service Engineer, you will mainly be carrying out warranty measures on M33 trams at the depot Slottsskogen in southern Gothenburg. The tasks are varied and include warranty repairs, troubleshooting, modifications and commissioning of M33 trams. Shifts occur and you will work with competent and committed colleagues who will help you get into the work and the team in the best way. There are works in the customer's other depots (depot Rantorget & depot Majorna).

What your mission includes:
Perform troubleshooting and warranty repairs of M33 trams. Carry out testing and commissioning of vehicles according to instructions. Manage technical surveys. Handle reporting of field data as well as other administration of forms etc. Support maintenance documentation validation. Be up to date regarding changes in maintenance documentation.
Perform modifications according to instruction and drawing documentation in English.
In English , register completed warranty work and root cause analyses in our digital maintenance system Maximo

Your profile?

As a service engineer, it is of great importance that you are driven and have a solid technical interest and ability to solve complex problems. We are looking for you who have experience of technical work from the automation industry, aviation, trains or the like where repair & troubleshooting of mechanical, electrical and digital control systems belongs to your everyday life.
Minimum qualifications:
Graduate in Engineering with a minimum 5 years of technical experience, either mechanical or electrical / electronic engineering
EHS knowledge/exposure
Product knowledge
Data analytics
Fluent in English & Swedish
Ideally:
Railway knowledge
Field Experience
Problem Solving skills

Why Alstom?
Alstom is the leading company in the railway sector, solving the most interesting challenges for tomorrow’s mobility. That’s why we value inquisitive and innovative people who are passionate about working together to reinvent mobility, making it smarter and more sustainable. Day after day, we are building an agile, inclusive and responsible culture, where a diverse group of people are offered opportunities to learn, grow and advance in their careers, with options across functions and geographic locations. Are you ready to join a truly international community of great people on a challenging journey with a tangible impact and purpose?

Alstom is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive working environment where all our employees are encouraged to reach their full potential, and individual differences are valued and respected. All qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by local law.

Title: SoMe Manager
Description:
Author William
Published 2022-07-02
Well, hello there!
We’re couldn’t be happier that you found us and we’re always looking for amazing social media managers to join us.
We don’t care if you work from the office, your home or from the middle of the ocean.
We don’t care where you’re from.
We do care about you, your skills, drive and if you’d fit in with us!
Skills
Plan, analyse and optimise content for our clients’ social media channels
Setting up and manage campaigns and manage a SoMe budget
Comfortable interacting with clients and other stakeholders
Knowledge of different SoMe channels and their unique features, limitations and potential
Nice to haves
Experience with Meta Business Manager, Google Adwords, etc
Have studied or have a keen interest in marketing
Experience with managing content on Facebook, Instagram, TikTok, YouTube, etc.
Other languages besides English is always a plus!
The role and you
You’ll be joining us in managing the social profiles for our amazing clients. What you don’t already know, you’ll learn on the job! In short, it’s all about getting a feel for the client and their brand so you can make their socials grow like crazy. We work with international clients so we’d love it if you speak English. This role will require you to have direct contact with our clients. We think you’re social, fun loving and like to come up with creative ideas – and love showing them off. If you’re someone who loves data, analytics and creating kick ass campaigns while delivering on time, you’ll fit right in.
We can’t wait to hear from you!

Title: MSc thesis in Artificial intelligence-driven condition monitoring and anomaly detection
Description:
MSc thesis in Artificial intelligence-driven condition monitoring and anomaly detection
Take your next career step at ABB with a global team that is energizing the transformation of society and industry to achieve a more productive, sustainable future. At ABB, we have the clear goal of driving diversity and inclusion across all dimensions: gender, LGBTQ+, abilities, ethnicity and generations. Together, we are embarking on a journey where each and every one of us, individually and collectively, welcomes and celebrates individual differences.

The industrial sector has been revolutionized by the recent technological advances in digitalization. Leveraging data analytics has now enabled the collection of deep insights into the performance and, as a result, the optimization of assets. Next generation industrial embedded systems are now capable of running machine learning models on the edge or extracting and transmitting post-processed signals to cloud computing services. The questions to be answered are to what extent the above points can be implemented in modern industrial systems and how effectively such models can perform. The purpose of this placement is to explore the capabilities of machine learning models for monitoring the condition of the next-generation industrial embedded systems and optimizing their performance. Developing and implementing ML models on edge devices or cloud services are also part of this placement. Details: • Period: February-July 2023 • 30 ECTS per student • Number of students: 1 • Location: On site ABB Corporate Research in Västerås, Sweden
Your responsibilities
Explore machine learning (ML) models for anomaly detection (e.g., temperature) and condition monitoring.
Design a neural network structure and identify the required inputs and parameters.
Develop and train an ML model – get access to a high-performance computing device.
Implement the model in commercially available devices or ABB products.
Be involved in lab testing for acquiring the training data and validating the model performance.
Investigate transfer learning methods and ways of generalizing the model.
Possibly publish the results of the work.
Your background
Intrinsically motivated, ambitious and possible to work independently (desirable).
Willing to build or improve programming skills in Python.
Prior knowledge of machine learning or electric drives is not a requirement, but a plus.
An existing ML model can be used as the foundation/starting point of this activity.
Motor and power electronics are the focus initially.
More about us
Recruiting Manager Dmitry Svechkarenko, +4621-34 51 73, will answer your questions about the position. We look forward to receiving your application (documents submitted in English are appreciated). If you want to discover more about ABB, take another look at our website www.abb.com.

Title: Business Intelligence Specialist
Description:
Vill du vara med och driva utvecklingen för börsens största fastighetsbolag? Är du en passionerad problemlösare med kärlek för data och hur detta kan skapa affärsvärde? Balder är ett spännande företag som fortsätter att växa och utvecklas i snabb takt. Den snabba utvecklingen beror på nyinvesteringar, men också på att man hos oss får möjligheten att utmana gamla sanningar och utveckla nya idéer. Bland dessa initiativ pågår ju nu en resa för att bli ännu mer data-drivna i alla våra beslut.
Vad mer konkret innebär rollen som Business Intelligence Specialist? I samband med vår satsning inom data och analys söker vi nu en Business Intelligence Specialist för vår data- och analysplattform som kommer arbeta nära både IT och affären för att facilitera utvecklingen av plattformen. Du kommer vara en del av teamet ”Data & Analytics” som faller inom avdelningen för affärsutveckling och IT. I rollen kommer du bland annat arbete med att:
Driva och vara delaktig i hela processer: från problemformulering till att hitta en lösning och slutprodukt. Detta gör det viktigt att man känner sig trygg i att äga och driva projekt från start till slut.
Skapa lösningar utifrån de affärskrav som finns från affärsverksamheten.
Sätta arkitekturen tillsammans med våra externa konsulter för att på kunna tillgodose organisationen med insikter som möjliggör lönsamma beslut.
Förvaltningen och utvecklingen av datalagret samt att vara involverad i tillhörande frontend-lösningar (framför allt Power BI).
Vi tror att du har tidigare erfarenhet av exempelvis ETL-utveckling (SQL), datamodellering enligt best-practise för datalager samt visualisering i Power BI inklusive uttryck i DAX. Kanske har du arbetat med underhåll av datalager samt testning och validering av datakvantitet och logik?
Det är extra meriterande om du har erfarenhet av Data Warehouse Automation (DWA), exempelvis Timextender. Vi har flyttat upp allt i molnet och vi ser därför gärna att du har koll på Azure-stacken och tillhörande IT-infrastruktur. Har du arbetat med ML/AI, API:er, eller data management är det en extra bonus. God kunskap i svenska är ett krav.
Du kommer att bli en del av ett team med höga ambitioner som är under en spännande tillväxtfas. Här är man kreativa problemlösare som har ett stort intresse kring vad data kan göra för affärsverksamheten. Men för att bli bäst behöver vi också tänka nytt. Därför söker vi dig som är utvecklingsfokuserad, prestigelös och som ständigt vill utmana. Vi har få begränsningar och är inte budgetstyrda. Vi ser fram emot dina idéer och att se dem bli till verklighet.
Vi är inte som andra fastighetsbolag. Vi är Balder. Idag är vi Nordens största börsnoterade fastighetsbolag och vår resa är inte slut än. Gillar du vårt affärsdriv, vår bredd och vår fart? Då kommer du säkert att trivas hos oss. Vi började vår resa 2005 med ett fastighetsbestånd värt 213 miljarder och idag är det få som hinner hålla koll exakt på vad beståndet är värt. För oss är det nämligen resan som är målet. Vill du hänga på?
Låter detta som en tjänst för dig? Härligt! Vi intervjuar löpande så ansök gärna redan idag. För att säkerställa ett objektivt rekryteringsunderlag kommer du att få genomföra rekryteringtester i processen. Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning. Har du frågor om tjänsten är du varmt välkommen att kontakta Kevin Larsson på 08-73 53 773 eller kevin.larsson@balder.se
Hjärtligt välkommen att bli en del av Balder och en bransch som är full av möjligheter. Vi ser fram emot din ansökan!

Avdelning
DITA (digitalisering, IT samt affärsutveckling)
Platser
Göteborg, Stockholm

Title: Ericsson Early Career Program | Excellerate | Commercial Manager
Description:
About this opportunity

Our Excellerate Global Leadership Program will give you an outstanding opportunity to engage with commercial projects at a strategic and global level, rising up to challenges and becoming and developing as a leader.

As part of the Excellerate program you are able to seize the initiative, operate with a consultative approach and collaborate on cross-technology solutions. The program will ensure you gain real practical insight into our business, our stakeholders and our customers including communication service providers (CSP) across the globe, and how we integrate end-to-end solutions to ensure everyone worldwide is connected.

Your journey within the Excellerate Program will start as Commercial Manager, part of the Commercial Management team at the Business Area Networks!

What you will do

At Business Area Network, Network Sales and Commercial Management (S&CM), our responsibilities are: Commercial Management, Sales and Commercial Strategies and Strategy Execution, and Commercial Analytics to enable fact-based decision making.

This is an outstanding opportunity to join a Commercial Management team, working to develop the commercial strategy including price models, price levels and Terms & Conditions for Ericsson Networks Portfolio, take them to market by commercial expert team members, and investigate commercial performance and trends with the help of data analytics. This role is an exciting mix of frontline commercial execution and a long-term strategic approach. You’ll gain a comprehensive view of the various dimensions of Ericsson operations, experiencing different functions and understanding exactly what it takes to be a globally oriented leader. From the beginning, you’ll thrive on early responsibility, embrace freedom and autonomy and encourage leadership to solve problems.

Upon completion of the program, you will have the skills to lead virtual global teams, drive exciting projects forward and become a leader in implementing pioneering information communication technology! In addition, you will have the opportunity to:

Lead/Co-Drive one or more key initiatives, often covering Hardware, Software and Services price models, commercial strategies with the goal of enhancing the monetization of our products
Use your strong analytical thinking and experience with data analytics to explore commercial trends for a global product portfolio
Present insights, conclusions, and recommendations to Ericsson leaders to improve the business at a global scale
Challenge status quo based on facts and logical reasoning, along with motivate change with new insights as a way for Ericsson to become more efficient
Manage and report on key activities by engaging people in different parts of the organization, developing your own leadership skills as well as delivering results in time and with quality
Balance multiple tasks in parallel, handling pressure and managing dynamic prioritization
Analyse market trends and finding significant insights to develop
You will bring

Your personal qualities are important for us, and we believe you are curious, innovative and collaborative. You have a motivation to work proactively, open, and dedicated with a keen interest to learn and to broaden experience and passion when bringing your ideas to the table.

In addition, we believe you have:

BSc or MSc in Industrial Engineering & Management, Information Technology, MBA degree or equivalent
The ability to extract insights out of complex information and present them in a simplified way
Solid presentation skills in English language, with ability to smoothly adapt to the respective audience to convey your message
Comfortable working in MS PowerPoint and MS Excel
Data analysis and visualization skills (for taking a role in Commercial Analytics)
An appetite to work in a fast-paced commercial environment

Be the one who did. Find out more about our Early Career program, what the alumni's are up to now and how the program can transform your career at www.ericsson.com/ecp

Why join Ericsson?

We are a world leader in the constantly evolving environment of communications technology – by providing hardware, software, and services to enable the full value of connectivity. You’ll play a part in using your skills and creativity to push the boundaries of what’s possible. To create never-seen-before solutions to some of the world’s toughest problems.

Join a team of innovators driven to go beyond the norm to build what’s next. At Ericsson, you can be an explorer, a change maker and a force for good.

What happens once you apply?

Click Here to find all you need to know about what our typical hiring process looks like. This role will have its first rotation in Kista Stockholm, Sweden. The selection and interview process is ongoing, so send your application in English as soon as it is ready. For questions or thoughts, reach out to Mathilda Jarl, Recruiter at mathilda.jarl@ericsson.com. Vetting including references and relevant background screening will be conducted for final candidates. We encourage the opportunity to meet you!

Encouraging a diverse and inclusive organization is core to our values at Ericsson, that's why we nurture it in everything we do. We truly believe that by collaborating with people with different experiences we drive innovation, which is essential for our future growth. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and realize their full potential as part of our Ericsson team. Ericsson is proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer, learn more.
Primary country and city: Sweden (SE) || Sweden : Stockholm : Stockholm
Req ID: 703962

Title: Global QC Lead - Process Analytical Technology
Description:
Are you ready for an opportunity to join AstraZeneca in a lead role with a focus on leading the deployment and integration of enhanced control strategies for continuous manufacturing? Are you seeking a leadership opportunity to push the boundaries of science, transforming our operation to the factory of the future which incorporates advanced analytical capabilities in process analytical technology (PAT) and predictive methods of analysis, and growing our science and technology capabilities?
We are looking for a talented Global QC Lead - Process Analytical Technology (PAT), to strengthen our capabilities in the area of analytical science towards control strategies developed using an enhanced approach. If you believe that you have operations Quality and manufacturing knowledge based in science then join us in our Global Quality & Stability organization! This role will have global responsibilities and can be based at our site in Sweden or globally.
Here at Global Quality & Stability, we work at the forefront of advanced technologies and digitalization with a focus on delivering high quality medicines to our patients leveraging our talented and diverse global team. We are always looking for creative and innovate ways to ensure we can consistently meet our patient’s needs.
Our organization, The Global Quality & Stability group owns, the delivery of Global Quality Control Strategy to improve and sustain the Global QC operation with processes to enable efficient delivery of safe and effective medicines to patients. We proactively integrates quality into our supply chain advancing beyond our compliance license to operate. We are accountable for the following areas:
Global Quality Control
Global Stability
Global Microbiology
Global Materials Certification
What you’ll do
This position will give you the opportunity to work in a dynamic and enthusiastic atmosphere, whilst leading in the deployment and application of process analytical technologies to enable enhanced control strategies in support of AstraZeneca’s product portfolio. In this role you will work closely with a team of colleagues in a multi-skilled environment to operationalize in our commercial production facilities ensuring appropriate quality management systems are in place to support using of PAT methods including model predictive controls, advanced process control, multi-variate data analytics, and predictive models. Continuous improvement will be at the core of everything you do, and you will support the PAT Strategy and advanced process control (including model predictive controls/APC/MVDA) to ensure that our organization is on the frontline of emerging technologies and tools, including continuous manufacturing & digital transformation. This position will give you the chance to lead and set clear direction for the organization in “cutting edge” areas , advising others at a high level, and being at the fore-front of external interactions.
The role will deliver on the following objectives:
Application of PAT to capitalize on product lifecycle management opportunities.
Identification of manufacturing process monitoring step data and correlated to QC results, that can be used for regulatory submissions and business cases for change
Product launch considerations with PAT from development through to regulatory submission
Sustainability improvements through PAT applications
Lead time improvements associated with PAT control and NPI launches
Industry benchmarking and external advocacy position papers
Serve as an expert/leader within Global Quality & Stability Organization, mentor colleagues in the area of enhanced control strategies and Process Analytical Technology (PAT), operationalizing our PAT Strategy transforming our business.
Provide direction and advice on new science and technology within Quality Operations of enhanced control strategies with PAT, to take part in tech transfer of these advanced analytical methods.
Continue to drive scientific excellence in the area of process analytical technology and advanced process control methodologies and technologies within the company. Provide leadership, coaching and mentorship to the QC Network other cross-functional colleagues.
Contribute to regulatory documentation and post approval submissions, applying your understanding of quality and operational knowledge to requirements from medical authorities.
Essential for the role
The Global QC Lead - PAT will implement new in-line, on-line and at-line real time or “near” real time analytical technology to support commercial manufacturing processes for a wide variety of molecules and modalities. Have a strong technical background in spectroscopy (Raman, FTIR, NIR, impedance), multivariate (chemometrics) modeling skills and/or process control for pharmaceutical API or Pharmaceutical processing and hands-on-experience and in-depth understanding of PAT concepts and its application to API or Pharmaceutical.

Qualifications for this role include:
Holds a minimum of Degree level in Pure or Applied Science (e.g., Biology, Chemistry, Pharmacy, Chemical Engineering) or other relevant scientific discipline and experience.
A minimum of 10 years’ experience in the pharmaceutical / bio-pharmaceutical industry, including having direct site experience in Quality and GMP associated with the manufacture of Drug Product or Drug Substance.
Sound knowledge and understanding of the principles and concepts of GMP, quality and compliance management, quality risk management and performance evaluation and control.
Familiar with FTIR, NIR, Raman, particle size, UV and other measurement techniques that are suitable for PAT applications. Hands-on-experience and in-depth understanding of PAT concepts and its application to pharmaceutical development. Demonstrated experience with statistics, chemometrics, programming and data modeling packages such as Matlab, Unscrambler, Eigenvector PLS Toolbox, JMP etc.
Desirable for the role
Significant experience within the field of Process Analytical Technology (PAT), advanced process control and/or chemometrics , analytical sciences or similar discipline, ideally with specialism in an area relevant to application of PAT to support continuous manufacturing. Demonstrated leadership with direct/indirect management of highly skilled workforce is highly desirable.
Demonstrated delivery of process analytical technology including advanced process control/MVDA, model predictive controls in support of pharmaceutical continuous processing. Well versed in ICH Q8, Q9, Q10, Q11 and Q13 guidance’s, Quality by Design principles, implementation of enhanced approaches for project/product specific control strategies.
Experience in technology transfer and commercial manufacture using continuous processing.
Experience in providing support for regulatory submissions (e.g. Investigational New Drug Applications, New Drug Applications).

Why AstraZeneca?
There are many opportunities to develop yourself and your career. From our diverse portfolio and teamwork to our cutting-edge innovations – it’s a place for lifelong learning. Ultimately, it’s more than a job. We know that our work impacts people with serious conditions, many of whom have no other alternatives. That’s what drives us – the potential to impact over one billion patients worldwide.

Title: Senior Programmatic Trading Specialist
Description:
The Trade Desk is changing the way global brands and their agencies advertise to audiences around the world. How? With a media buying platform that helps brands deliver a more insightful and relevant ad experience for consumers – and sets a new standard for global reach, accuracy, and transparency. We are proud of the culture we have built. We value the unique experiences and perspectives that each person brings to The Trade Desk, and we are committed to fostering inclusive spaces where everyone can bring their authentic selves to work every day.
So, if you are talented, driven, creative, and eager to join a dynamic, globally-connected team, then we want to talk!
Who We Are:

The Trade Desk is leading the way to the future of marketing by changing how advertising is bought and sold. Working with the largest brands and agencies around the world, our technology platform helps consumers discover products they want by enabling advertisers to target and reach them on the right channels at the right time.

Our platform enables ad buyers to create, manage, and optimise data-driven digital advertising campaigns across all channels, including connected TV. We offer unparalleled audience scale and reach, evaluating nearly nine million queries across the internet every second. It is the unique combination of the power of our platform and the expertise of our people that puts our customers in a position to succeed.

Employees join The Trade Desk to discover opportunity, contribute to our customers’ success, and be part of building the future of marketing. You’ll work with creative, compassionate, and collaborative colleagues that share a passion for making the internet better for all – a combination that simply can't be beat.

When you join The Trade Desk, you’re joining a family. We have open space work environments, adjustable sitting/standing desks, and a celebrated open-door policy (at all levels) that can inspire out-of-the-box solutions and camaraderie among your coworkers. The competitive compensation packages, full benefits, stock options, and additional discounted stock purchase opportunities, catered lunches, and offsite team building activities may cause slight to severe jealousy among your peers.

WHAT YOU’LL DO:
Become an expert on The Trade Desk platform and best practices for campaign management
Play a core role in growing business of assigned client portfolio
Combine data analysis and client feedback to create optimisation strategies and provide the most effective solutions for campaigns
Understand and communicate The Trade Desk’s value proposition, technology, and partnerships, to help grow clients’ accounts
Partner with Account Management and Business Development to provide support to clients, including onboarding, optimisation and reporting training
Work with Product Management to help define features and drive enhancements to The Trade Desk platform
Become a thought leader in digital media strategy and optimisation – and the programmatic advertising industry in general

WHO YOU ARE:
Extensive programmatic and data analytics experience in the Nordic region and/or trading experience with other Demand-Side Platforms is a plus.
Solid client-facing & client management experience is essential.
Outstanding troubleshooting, analytical, and problem-solving abilities, along with the skills to collaborate cross-functionally in a fast-paced environment
Self-starter, with a strong can-do attitude.
Effective time management and organisation skills – ability to prioritise and meet deadlines, and to work within an hybrid setup.
Strategic mindset with the ability to look for opportunities for improvements and changes.
Strong story telling skills.
Advanced MS Excel skills. Other data analytics skills like SQL, R or Python can be an advantage.
Strong quantitative skills and the ability to draw insights from extremely large datasets.
Ability to thrive in a small, intense, and high growth environment.
The Trade Desk does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firm recruiters. Fees will not be paid in the event a candidate submitted by a recruiter without an agreement in place is hired; such resumes will be deemed the sole property of The Trade Desk. The Trade Desk is an equal opportunity employer. All aspects of employment will be based on merit, competence, performance, and business needs. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, marital status, age, national origin, ancestry, physical or mental disability, medical condition, pregnancy, genetic information, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, or any other status protected under federal, state, or local law.

Title: Digital Marketing Coordinator
Description:
For our HQ in Malmö, we are now looking for a data-driven Digital Marketing Coordinator that can support us with multiple marketing activities. Join us for an exciting journey to strengthen our brand and make a significant contribution to our future growth!

About the role:
This is a brand new role with a lot of fun opportunities! You will be a part of our Marketing team and work closely with our Chief Marketing & Innovation Officer and occasionally with our People Experience Associate. You will support our entities in Sweden and Germany with a global focus. Even though this is a student position, you will be given great responsibility and be our go-to person for our marketing activities such as SEO, website, copy & content, Google ads etc. We will continue to grow in the future, which means that this role could develop into a full-time position.

Key tasks (among others):
Work with content & copy in our social media channels with support from Marketing and HR (and keep our SoMe-calender up-to-date)
SEO and data analytics, data insights
Work with and maintain our website in WordPress
Support Employer Branding activities
Advertising and campaign management in Google Ads and LinkedIn
Eventually identify and evaluate new digital technologies and optimize the website strategy, marketing campaigns, social media, and display & search advertising using web analytics tools
Eventually develop, implement, and manage the marketing strategy and campaigns
Eventually develop our global social media plan

We realize that you can’t spread yourself too thin, but we want to highlight our ambition from a long-term perspective.

Who do we think you are to succeed in this role?
Fluent in English
Studying digital marketing or equal with at least 1 year left on the program
Interest in social media trends
Good IT skills
Credible and confident communicator (written and verbal) at all levels
First-class planning, organizational, and time management skills
Experienced in working with analysis tools such as Google Analytics
Familiar working with LinkedIn

What’s in it for you?
As an employee, we are committed to providing you with a wide range of real-world experiences and responsibilities that will accelerate your learning curve and give you tools for future success. You will have the opportunity to learn, explore, and gain hands-on experience in digital marketing and make a real impact on the company. Also, you will have an exceptional opportunity to influence the team’s future success through your ideas and contributions and be part of a very enthusiastic and open-minded team with highly skilled colleagues.

If you’re passionate about being a part of a flat networked organisation that works to find innovative solutions to health care challenges and want to be a part of a tightly knit team, we look forward to your application.

About us:
Magle Chemoswed is a contract development and manufacturing organization with a strong track record of bringing new products to the market for its customers in the global pharmaceutical and medical device industry. The company provides CDMO services ranging from product development to full scale commercial manufacturing. By owning its manufacturing and development facilities, the company has all the resources required to successfully manage CDMO work in the pharmaceutical and medical device fields.

Other information:
Start date: January/February
Location: Malmö
15-20 hours/week

Applications should be sent to nellie.mansson@maglechemoswed.com. We will review applications on an ongoing basis. We look forward to speaking to you soon. For questions, please contact Nellie Månsson, the People Experience Associate.

Title: Product Manager – Data Optimization
Description:
Pushing boundaries for a sustainable future
The world is dealing with an environmental crisis and energy crisis, and we, as Vargas Holding’s latest venture, are actively creating a sustainable future. We provide renewable energy solutions to everyday homes to help them cut their dependency on oil and gas, electrify their energy consumption, and to control their energy bill. To solve the climate and energy crisis, we are at the forefront of creating innovative solutions that accelerate the creation of smart and sustainable homes.
Heating alone represents some 15% of the EU's CO2 emissions and switching to a sustainable energy solution is by far the easiest way for a household to make a real impact. That's why we are dedicated to developing solutions that not only combat these crises and create sustainable homes but also empower homeowners to take control of their energy consumption and save money on their energy bills.
Our goal is to cut homeowners’ dependency on fossil fuels and help them transition to clean, renewable energy sources. We make it possible for everyone to combat the climate crisis. With a firm belief in the power of innovation and technology, we build solutions for today’s challenges, and for those of tomorrow – for current and our next generations. By transforming local energy consumption, we will create a global transformation.
We are passionate about making a positive impact on the world, and we believe that by creating smart and sustainable homes, we can do just that. We hope you will join us in this important work as we strive to make a difference in the fight against the climate crisis.

About the role
We are expanding our Engagement team where we focus on creating an engaging experience for our customers when they have their energy solution installed at home. We are looking for PO who can help us drive and build our data platform needed for our product experience. This includes identifying needed sources, gathering, cleaning, transforming, and normalizing of this data. We want to visualize this data to our users making the energy consumption clear to our customers, as well as using this data to help our customer to more sustainable consumption patterns.
As our Product Manager focusing on an engaging client experience you will lead a dedicated team of engineers and designers who work together to define, prioritize, measure, experiment, adjust and deliver on our product vision for our customer-facing apps and web. You need to understand our customer pain points, investigate possible solutions, prioritize, develop, deploy, measure results, learn, and adjust in iterations to remove value barriers and deliver our product's greatest impact.
With a special focus on data optimization for our application, you will be responsible for driving the development of features and capabilities that maximize the value of the data collected by our system. In short, you will be responsible for the gathering and structure of the data, as well as the ML modeling for energy saving optimizations.
Your other responsibilities include:
In collaboration with other departments create user journeys
Identify gaps in our user journeys
Creating product requirements and specifications
Backlog management and iteration planning
Lead the team and their development priorities, and drive feature, application, and product releases

What we would like you to have
From a technical perspective we would like you to have:
3-5 years of experience as a product owner/manager
Strong understanding of data analytics and visualization tools and techniques
Experience with data-driven product development
Experience working with large and complex datasets
Familiarity with SQL or other database querying languages
Experience with agile software development methodologies
Experience of digital services for the consumer market, mobile apps, apps controlling hardware, and/or smart home solutions.
We would even appreciate it if you have some experience with/knowledge of some of the following:
Experience with similar growth teams of a platform or application
Experience working at fast-growing scale-ups
Experience of innovative data visualization
Experience from the energy sector
Experience from telemetric intense systems/setups, and IOT
As a person we would like you to be:
High ambition, initiative, and entrepreneurial mindset (self-starter)
A personality who thrives in an ever-changing environment and can create structure from the ground up
Fast-moving and solution-oriented
Analytical skills
Strong leadership abilities to inspire and motivate.

What we offer
Besides a competitive salary and secondary benefits, we offer the opportunity to build a global company and product with true environmental impact. Our team is led by top engineers from IKEA, Volvo, Scania, Viaplay, and Kry, bringing a wealth of experience and expertise to the table.
As a member of our team, you'll have the chance to be a part of a fast-moving growth journey with far-reaching learning and development opportunities. You'll have the chance to work with some of the most talented and innovative professionals in the industry, dedicated to making a positive impact on the world through our products and services. You'll be able to contribute to the development of cutting-edge technology that has the potential to make a significant positive impact on the world.
In addition to the opportunity to contribute to a meaningful and impactful company, you'll also have access to ongoing learning and development opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally. We believe that our team is our greatest asset, and we are committed to fostering a supportive and inclusive culture that empowers our employees to reach their full potential.
Whether you're an experienced professional or just starting out in your career, we believe that everyone has the potential to make a meaningful contribution to our mission. So, if you're passionate about building a better future and want to be a part of something special, we'd love to have you join us. So, come and join our team and be a part of building a truly global company with a product that makes a real difference in the world.

Don't hesitate and send us your application today! If you have any questions regarding applications or else, contact me at rolf.kusch@vargasholding.se

Title: Data consultant - Stockholm
Description:
The main focus of the company is on Business Intelligence, Data, Analytics, AI/ML and RPA.

They are working across all industries notable customers/industries include: Telia, Volvo, Stina, Chalmers, Government, Western Region, Accounting, H&M, Pfizer, Klarna, Banking/Finance.

Our client is growing their company, adding new projects constantly and is looking forward to expanding their team with Data Consultants, who would help them to manage all their projects on time.

They want you to be a specialist in one field but would need you to have an ambition or understanding to learn something else and therefore broaden your technical knowledge.

Skills & Qualifications

Understanding technical/data requirements
Data modelling and analysis
Working with cloud solutions: Azure, AWS or GCP
* Building dashboards and visualisations: Qlik* or Power BI*
Speaking with the customer
Fluent in Swedish

Benefits

Wellness allowance
Pension
Health insurance
Car allowance
Laptop and mobile, etc.

Our client has offices in Stockholm, Malmo, Gothenburg, Orebro, Jonkoping and a few other cities in Sweden in that case working remote would be an option for this position. However, you have to be based in Sweden in case you have to go to the office at some time for team activities and occasional travel to the customers office.

Even if this is not the exact role you are looking for, get in touch anyway, and just highlight what you are looking for. Please apply with your CV and a brief overview of what you are looking for (the role, top 3 technologies, location, salary). I will call you to discuss your skill-set further, there may be other roles I am working on that you may be suited for. Here at Nigel Frank International, I focus on the recruitment of highly-skilled professionals in various IT positions such as Engineers, Analysts, Architects, Consultants, etc. That is why we always have new opportunities pop up.

Email: g.zelionyte@nigelfrank.com

LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/gintare-zelionyte-55546419/

Nigel Frank International is the global leader in Microsoft technology recruitment. Since 2006, we've found over 19,000 permanent and contract Microsoft professionals for partners, ISVs, and end users in the ecosystem. For more information, visit www.nigelfrank.com.

Sweden
Pension, health insurance, laptop and mobile.
Consultant Role
Level: Mid-level

Title: Data Engineer till Marginalen Bank!
Description:
Motiveras du av att driva transformering där molnresan står i fokus? Trivs du som bäst när du får arbeta med både tekniska lösningar och arkitekturella strategier? Då ser vi gärna att du läser vidare…

Som Data Engineer har du en nyckelroll i bankens resa mot en mer datadriven organisation. Du är en del av Data Automation-teamet inom vår centrala Data & Analytics organisation, där även Data Science och Modellering & Analys-teamen ingår.

Det här är rollen för dig som vill kombinera erfarenhet av hands-on utveckling med arkitektur och strategi.
Rollen är baserad på huvudkontoret i Stockholm men möjlighet till visst arbete hemifrån finns.
Ett urval av dina kommande arbetsuppgifter…

Som Data Engineer arbetar du i ett av våra scrum team inom Data Automation teamet men även med andra funktioner med bankens datastrategi. I rollen arbetar du tillsammans med teamet för att skapa strategier och förutsättningar för Marginalen Banks förflyttning till molnet och möjliggörandet av datadrivna beslut, processer, rapportering och ökad affärsintelligens inom hela banken. Teamet består även av konsulter från andra länder än Sverige. Därav är det ett krav att kunna föra sig i tal och skrift på engelska.
Vem du är…
För att lyckas i rollen ser vi att du har erfarenhet av automatisering, versionshantering och DevOps. Du bör även ha erfarenhet av Azure och några av dess komponenter, exempelvis: Azure Data Factory och Azure Data Lake. Även erfarenhet av Snowflake och GIT är meriterande. Du kanske även har ett intresse och/eller erfarenhet av datamodellering (Data Vault, Kimball, Inmon).
Du är van att arbeta agilt och din nyfikenhet och intresse gör att du ständigt håller dig uppdaterad inom ditt område och på nya tekniker. Du ser lösningar framför hinder och brinner för att kombinera dina tekniska kunskaper med att driva och att påverka. Du trivs att jobba i team, är prestigelös och delar kunskap och hjälper andra på ett ödmjukt sätt.
Vad Marginalen Bank erbjuder dig…
Hos oss blir du en del av en prestigelös organisation där du förutsätts delta aktivt samt påverka processer och rutiner. Vi arbetar agilt och skapar effektiva lösningar och fattar goda och genomtänkta beslut. Vi är innovativa, har hög moral, tänker och agerar hållbart, arbetar proaktivt och driver igenom fattade beslut med en handlingskraft och i tid.
Vårt huvudkontor, mitt i centrala Stockholm, huserar i byggnaden Grönlandet - ett arkitektoniskt mästerverk signerat Sigurd Lewerentz från 1932. Vi har en egen restaurang som lagar ekologisk mat vilket är en extra lyx i vår vardag! Här får du arbeta med medarbetare som känner stolthet, arbetsglädje och delaktighet. Vi erbjuder också personlig utveckling ,volontärdag, tjänstepension, friskvårdsbidrag och hälsoförsäkring vilket bara är några av alla våra förmåner. - Läs gärna mer om vår kultur, våra värdeord och våra förmåner på vår hemsida.
Låter detta som något för dig, tveka då inte att kontakta oss!
Vid eventuella frågor är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande ledare Jonathan Söderström på Jonathan.Soderstrom@Marginalen.se. Då urvalsprocessen sker löpande är du varmt välkommen med din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast den 15-03-2023.

Title: Game - Marketing - Event Manager
Description:
Landell Games AB was established in 2021 and performs consulting work in IT such as infrastructure, due diligence, and the manufacture of software such as video games and innovative technology.
We are currently looking for an Event Manager that would help our Community Manager with their day-to-day tasks and would join us for 6 months part-time (minimum 20h/week) or full-time with the opportunity to extend it further,
and since we are in discussions with big names in the video game industry, we plan to start our recruitment process shortly.
It is however important to note that the internship period is unpaid and is fully remote.
Our Marketing Team is growing fast and we are in need of a person who would take care of the tasks revolving around virtual and physical events, as well as making sure that our newsletter and other content that we share with our community are up to date.
Your assignments would consist of helping the Community Manager with organizing events such as podcasts, Q&A events and game testing, as well as making sure that we are present on both virtual and physical events where we have a chance of promoting our game.
The most important attribute you need is a strong drive to learn and see things through, and if you are ready to put in sweat and tears, we are ready to provide you with a unique skill set that will help us reach our goals and help you build an impressive portfolio for your future endeavors in the gaming industry.
Examples of assignments:
- Hosting and overseeing Discord events such as playtesting, podcasts and Q&A events
- Keeping in touch with all teams and keeping track of all updates they find important so that we can properly inform our community
- Researching and analyzing the virtual and physical gaming related events that we should be a part of
- Making sure that every event enhances the brand-to-client experience
- Coming up with events that would allow us to network with customers, publishers, investors and other developers
Who are we:
We pride ourselves on being hardworking, determined and passionate.
Positive mindset and hunger for knowledge are in our blood and we are always happy to help each other out and welcome new members to the project.
The team itself works together remotely and has many years of combined experience in the growing gaming industry and is growing by the day, with more than 40 gaming enthusiasts currently working on the project. We are very open to sharing our knowledge and we encourage every member to be inquisitive about the methods and progress of their own team, as well as about the other departments. Voicing one's opinion is extremely important in our mission of game development and self betterment, so we see it as a quality of motivated individuals and welcome it on every occasion.
What we offer:
- Shape your own way of working and choose your working hours with us
- Get the opportunity to learn from practical experience in Marketing, namely Data Analytics and Event Management
- Work on an ambitious project that you can use in your portfolio
- Learn about developing a game as a whole - Make invaluable connections -
Have fun and hopefully make lifelong friendships
Who you are:
- First and foremost, a passionate gamer who sincerely wants an opportunity to work in the gaming industry
- An independent individual not afraid to ask questions, solve problems and address issues
- A creative, inquisitive and detail oriented person who is willing to make their own decisions and are genuinely excited to learn and develop their knowledge within marketing in gaming industry
Requirements:
- Fluency in English
- Basic understanding of Excel and/or Google sheets
- Basic understanding of Discord
- Willingness and ability to dedicate at least 20 hours a week to the project for the period of at least 6 months Additional (not required) skills:
- Experience with event management (in any industry)
- Experience with promoting gaming content on social media
- Basic understanding of Social Media insights and analytics
Read more about the game project at: https://DawnofEmpires.com Attach your Resume/CV together with a short description of why you would be the best fit for us.
We are looking forward to getting to know you better!
Jobbtyp: Heltid, Deltid, Vikariat, Praktik, Trainee
Arbetstider:
Måndag till fredag
Flexible Language Requirement:
Svenskkunskap krävs inte
Arbetsort: Distans

Title: Cloud Solution Architect – Data & AI
Description:
As a Cloud Solution Architect, you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers make the right decisions and give them a solid foundation to succeed on their journey.
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data has a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
We are partners with different technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of clients and technologies, together with amazing colleagues.
As a Cloud Solution Architect, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing optimal technical solutions.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients in the decision making of which platform and architecture to use
Integration of different data sources, modeling and loading of data
Optimizing different solutions (data warehouse, data lakehouse, machine learning) depending on the purpose
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
What we are looking for:
Hands on experience in setting up cloud architecture in Azure, AWS or GCP
Experience in architecting and designing data solutions using trade-off analysis
Knowledge of different information architecture patterns (e.g. dimensional model, data vault 2.0, data mesh, lakehouse)
Experience in DevOps tools including version control (Git), CI/CD pipelines and infrastructure as code (Terraform)
Experience in architecture governance and architecture documentation
Familiar with data management, data security, and access control in the cloud
Prototyping mindset and familiar with Python, Pyspark and SQL
Experience working with streaming data
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills.
What we see as qualifying:
Cloud architect certification or Databricks certification or willingness to undergo one on joining
Evidence of architectural trade off analysis
Hands on experience for designing data ingestion and transformation patterns in the cloud
DataOps solution design experience (observability, error handling)
Experience designing storage topologies, data models and optionally understanding of domain driven design
Experience working with cloud storage, cloud data pipeline tools, CDC tools and data catalogues
Stakeholder management

Title: Project Manager
Description:
Are you passionate about leading and developing business projects?
Are you a driven business developer with a strong entrepreneurial spirit?
Do you want to be part of a tech company’s international expansion?
Then you have found the right opportunity!
Greater Than is an award-winning Insurtech provider, developing AI and applications helping Insurance carriers and mobility providers to predict risk, reduce claims cost and award good driving. Our business is growing rapidly, and we need a skilled and experienced Project Manager within tech, who is passionate about leading business projects from start to in-market success.
Job description
As a Project Manager, you will be responsible for leading and developing business projects with our auto insurance, automotive and mobility customers globally. Within this role, you will work with our sales and tech team to map business opportunities, drive sales processes, and be the lead for our internal and external projects from start to ongoing success.
You will have the opportunity to use and develop your business acumen, lead cross-functional teams from start of an idea, to market launch, to ongoing development. You will lead parallel projects, within several regions and industries, with different deadlines and your responsibility will be to deliver your projects on time, at the right budget, according to specification and with excellent quality! You will work with passionate colleagues from several fields including full-stack, front-end and UX and be part of launching new apps, web and data analytics projects around the world.
This assignment is located in Japan, but might involve travel. You will report directly to our Head of Japan.
Who are we looking for
To succeed in the role, we believe that you have a strong entrepreneurial spirit, and can keep several parallel projects going on at the same time. You are business-oriented, with analytical skills, structured mindset and it’s natural for you to lead cross-functional teams. You have experience of project management and are driven by developing client relations. We believe that you feel strong compassion for our client’s needs and success and find it natural to build trust, inspire and build long-term relationships with the Greater Than team and our customers.
Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in project management - marketing - business administration - sales or relevant field
Fluent in Japanese & proficient in English
Min 3 years work experience within Project management or Business Development or Key Account Management
Good skills with Microsoft office
Analytical skills - project management skills - presentation skills
Experience working with SaaS is a plus
The team with us
With us, you work with a passionate team of 40+ people located globally. We are a fast-paced company and passionate about growing and developing our employees. The organisation is modernly led, and we approach a go-get mentality where we help each other and find areas for our employees to deepen their knowledge and accelerate their careers.
To apply please email: career@greaterthan.eu and attach your CV alongside with a motivation letter to why you want to join Greater Than. We will review candidates on an ongoing basis.

Title: Data Warehouse Developer Wanted at ICA Banken
Description:
Are you an experienced ETL Engineer looking for a new challenge? ICA Banken is seeking a skilled Data Warehouse Developer to join our team and work on our MS SQL-based Data Warehouse and ETL solutions. As a member of our Data Management team, you will work alongside 10 senior experts in projects and proactive maintenance to provide data-driven insights to business stakeholders and end-users.
ETL Engineering in a Transforming Platform
In this role, you will play a vital role in the entire process for design, development, and operations of a traditional Data Warehouse system. You will focus on ETL data flows, but also align data needs with staff working with reporting, visualization and analysis. You will additionally contribute to ICA Banken’s new transformation initiative for implementing modern capabilities for advanced analytics on a cloud platform.

Key Responsibilities include:
Identify and analyze source data to meet business requirements
Design and develop Data Warehouse data models and structures
Design and develop ETL procedures and architectures
SQL programming of system components
Perform incident and error handling for the Data Warehouse system in production

We are looking for you
We believe you have solid experience in data warehousing and willing to excel in a Data warehouse developer position. You have an engineering background or similar with SQL experience. Both Swedish and English skills are preferred. This role can be located at ICA Bankens HQ in Borås or at the office in Solna.

Apply now
Any kind of questions about the position contact hiring manager Johan Karlsson, Manager Data Analytics +4610 422 02 28, questions about the selection process or terms & conditions at ICA please contact recruiter Markus Koppari, +4672 220 28 31 or Markus Öhman +4676 695 62 04. Apply as soon as possible, but no later than. 2023-02-19.

About ICA Banken
We are an everyday bank that lasts longer. We create personal, simple and affordable services for the ICA customer. Every day. Our business concept is to make everyday life a little easier for ICA's customers through financial services, as well as increase customers’ loyalty to ICA and reduce the ICA stores' and ICA AB's transaction costs for foreign banks and credit cards.
During this recruitment process we will use online tools for your safety for interviews and getting to know your skills. We also apply drug testing and control of credit information before all new hires.

Title: Tech Lead for a Connected Features team within Autonomous...
Description:
For Zenseact it is a given that software deployed to cloud is a key part of our product. To solve the problem of true autonomy we need to leverage the power of not only individual vehicles, but entire fleets. We are challenging traditional ways of working with software within automotive to create a modern and leading eco-system of partners, data and end-user services around automated mobility.
Insights from the team
Our team is called Mimer, referring to a god in Norse mythology, renowned for his knowledge and wisdom ;). We are now growing the team and looking for a colleague who take pride in the art of developing great code for globally distributed and connected systems.
Currently we are four developers, with passion for areas such as security, optimization, Kubernetes and clean code. We work in an agile framework, with a product owner who demonstrates confidence in our ability to do the job, and with hands-on experience to chip in to our discussions. We work as a cross-functional team, where we collaborate tightly to have a common view on our strategy and the recommendations we provide. Far from being ivory towers, we work closely with the feature teams to provide guidance on a need basis, ensuring coherence where essential and hands on development of shared components.
Your Role
As a Tech Lead within the cloud and maps product-domain you will be a key person working with innovative connected features related to self-driving and advanced driver support. The role involves:
Leading and supporting teams in software and technical architecture work, specifically around cloud adoption
Create designs supporting both functional needs as well as taking care of performance, resilience, reuse, maintainability, scalability and security
Hands-on development of key functional components as well as tooling, patterns and guidelines
Drive process and tooling for CI/CD, verification and requirements

Your Profile
As a successful Tech Lead for Cloud and Maps at Zenseact you have a strong background in the full lifecycle of designing, developing, testing, deploying, operating and maintaining cloud based software solutions and managing individual project priorities, deadlines and deliverables. Furthermore, you have:
Experience building and operating large-scale systems in public cloud, specifically Microsoft Azure
Strong experience with one or more of Java, C++, python
Good communication and leadership skills
A self-starter with the ability to work effectively in teams and individually
Experience with any of this will give you an extra edge:
Cloud infrastructure automation, specifically Terraform
IoT or connected vehicle solutions
Stream analytics and processing technologies
Big data analytics
Mapping and GIS
IT Security
Operating global distributed system, especially including China

Why Zenseact?
Flexible-remote way of working: Zenseact has a flexible and modern approach, thus is happy to offer to its employees the possibility for a combination of work at the office and from home. This doesn't include fully remote work from outside Sweden/China.
More about Zenseact
Zenseact’s purpose is to make safe and intelligent mobility real, for everyone, everywhere. We develop the complete software stack for ADAS and AD, from sensing to actuation. Our focus is to build a single cutting-edge software platform in order to serve various levels of autonomy and offer unequaled scalability at the same time. We operate out of Gothenburg, Sweden and Shanghai, China. Zenseact’s first self-driving deployment will be launched on the next-generation vehicle platform from Volvo Cars.

Self-driving cars, when real, is estimated to reduce fatal car accidents with more than 85%, saving more than 50,000 persons from dying in car accidents caused by human errors each year. We feel that is a goal worth pursuing.

But technology, software, tools and datasets would not mean much without the best people behind the wheel to drive them. At Zenseact, some five hundred of the best engineering minds globally, stationed across two continents, are collaborating with the same passion: to bring autonomous driving to the streets for real and create a safer journey for everyone. This is part of our culture and how we work, develop and grow together.
Zenseact works proactively to create a culture of diversity and inclusion, where individual differences are appreciated and respected. To drive innovation we see diversity as an asset, which means we value and respect differences in gender, race, ethnicity, religion or other belief, disability, sexual orientation or age etc.

Interviews are held on a continuous basis, so we highly recommend that you submit your application at your earliest convenience.

Title: Project & Service Delivery Manager
Description:
Är du intresserad av projektledning och har en teknisk förståelse? Vill du vara med och leda utvecklings- och uppgraderingsprojekt hos våra kunder? Då kan rollen som Project & Service Delivery Manager vara något för dig!

Om rollen
I din vardag förväntas du vara projektansvarig för Innofactors kunder med ett helhetsansvar att leda, samordna och förbättra våra processer och vårt arbetssätt, såväl internt som externt, för att systematiskt öka effektiviteten, lönsamheten och kundnöjdheten.
Du ansvarar för kvaliteten i leveranserna och är involverad i strukturering och hantering av avtal samt ekonomisk uppföljning från början till slut. Det är också viktigt att du är tillräckligt tekniskt kunnig för att kunna ha en bra dialog med kund, särskilt inom CRM/ Dynamics 365.
För att lyckas i rollen som Project & Service Delivery Manager tror vi att du erfarenhet av agila metoder, är nyfiken, prestigelös, hjälpsam och drivs av att utveckla andra och att hitta förbättringsåtgärder i det dagliga arbetet.
I dina arbetsuppgifter ingår att planera, genomföra och följa upp projekt, där framtagning av projektplan och tidplan är en självklarhet, planera Workshop-arbete när det behövs och hålla backlogen strukturerad och uppdaterad.
Arbetsuppgifter
Du genomför sprintplanering, projektmöten och daglig avstämning samt hjälper utvecklingsteamet att eliminera hinder i deras vardagliga arbete
Du tar fram estimat tillsammans med andra intressenter i projektet, skapar budget och faktureringsunderlag som skickas till kund
Du är ett bollplank till projektgruppen och har en aktiv roll i framtagning av lösningsförslag, arkitektur och infrastruktur
Du genomför riskanalys inom projektet samt har en kontinuerlig uppföljning där du ständigt håller styrgrupp och projektmedlemmar informerade om status och eventuella avvikelser i projektet
Du agerar kontaktperson gentemot kund och är föredragande i styr- och ledningsgruppen
Du måste vara lyhörd och förstå kundens krav såväl som Innofactors behov i sakfrågor
Vi söker dig som
Har flerårig dokumenterad erfarenhet av rollen som projektledare, är teknisk, lösningsorienterad och har bra koll på hur olika system hänger ihop
Har god förståelse för IT och teknik, jobbat nära utvecklingsteam och kund samt drivit införande- och uppgraderingsprojekt
Har erfarenhet av, eller arbetat inom, förvaltningsledning utöver projektledning och har drivit, och kan driva, mer än ett projekt samtidigt
Är van vid kravställning och att samordna aktiviteter samt att fungera som bro för informationsflöden
Är van att arbeta nära utvecklingsteam och kund samt har stor förmåga att vägleda och stötta projektgruppen samt hjälpa beställare i kundens verksamhet
Har förmågan att lyfta blicken och se på projektet ur olika infallsvinklar när viktiga beslut ska fattas
Har ett kommunikativt ledarskap, är lyhörd och tydlig i din kommunikation
Är affärsmässig och förtroendeingivande och jobbar över gränserna, inspirerar och får med dig både kunden och den interna organisationen på tåget
Är självgående och strukturerad och van att arbeta mot tydliga mål och med ett tydligt lönsamhetsansvar
Har arbetat eller har erfarenhet inom Microsofts projektmodell Sure Step, PRINCE2, Scrum, Kanban, ITIL och har goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska
Det är också meriterande om du har arbetat med Microsofts produkter och ärendehantering så som JIRA eller DevOps. Eftersom Innofactor är ett konsultföretag är det också meriterande om du har erfarenhet av konsultarbete och arbete i kundprojekt.
Vi erbjuder
Innofactor har det bredaste erbjudandet i Microsofts ekosystem med expertkunskap hos 600 anställda i Norden. I Sverige är vi 100 erfarna och engagerade kollegor som arbetar med intressanta och utmanande projekt inom Microsoft Dynamics 365, Office 365, Microsoft Power Platform, Microsoft Data & Analytics Platform och Azure. Vi är en Microsoft Gold Partner i 15 kategorier och har fått utmärkelsen Microsoft Dynamics Partner, vilket vi är väldigt stolta över.
En kreativ och dynamisk arbetsplats där vi jobbar tillsammans, hjälper och utmanar varandra och har roligt på vägen. Tillsammans bildar vi ett starkt team för att möta marknadens krav på innovativa och avancerade verksamhetslösningar. Vårt huvudsakliga uppdrag är att ge både organisationer och individer chansen att göra skillnad i den digitala världen. Vi tycker också att det är viktigt att du som anställd får en bra balans mellan arbete och privatliv.
Vi har våra lokaler på Drottninggatan mitt i centrala Stockholm. Det finns även möjligheter att arbeta remote, om man önskar att utgå från sin hemadress. Innofactor är en arbetsplats där vi tror på ett ömsesidigt förtroende, respekt och stöd. Våra anställda står i centrum.
Är du intresserad? Skicka in din ansökan med CV och brev redan idag, så hör vi av oss.
Tillsättning sker löpande.
Om Innofactor
Innofactor är ett unikt Microsoft-fokuserat företag med över 600 anställda i Norden. På Innofactor Sverige får du arbeta med intressanta och utmanande projekt tillsammans med erfarna och engagerade kollegor. Vi hjälper företag och organisationer att öka sin lönsamhet och konkurrenskraft genom att integrera och effektivisera arbetsprocesser och verksamhetssystem.

Title: Ericsson Early Career Program | Excellerate | Commercial Manager
Description:
About this opportunity

Our Excellerate Global Leadership Program will give you an outstanding opportunity to engage with commercial projects at a strategic and global level, rising up to challenges and becoming and developing as a leader.

As part of the Excellerate program you are able to seize the initiative, operate with a consultative approach and collaborate on cross-technology solutions. The program will ensure you gain real practical insight into our business, our stakeholders and our customers including communication service providers (CSP) across the globe, and how we integrate end-to-end solutions to ensure everyone worldwide is connected.

Your journey within the Excellerate Program will start as Commercial Manager, part of the Commercial Management team at the Business Area Networks!

What you will do

At Business Area Network, Network Sales and Commercial Management (S&CM), our responsibilities are: Commercial Management, Sales and Commercial Strategies and Strategy Execution, and Commercial Analytics to enable fact-based decision making.

This is an outstanding opportunity to join a Commercial Management team, working to develop the commercial strategy including price models, price levels and Terms & Conditions for Ericsson Networks Portfolio, take them to market by commercial expert team members, and investigate commercial performance and trends with the help of data analytics. This role is an exciting mix of frontline commercial execution and a long-term strategic approach. You’ll gain a comprehensive view of the various dimensions of Ericsson operations, experiencing different functions and understanding exactly what it takes to be a globally oriented leader. From the beginning, you’ll thrive on early responsibility, embrace freedom and autonomy and encourage leadership to solve problems.

Upon completion of the program, you will have the skills to lead virtual global teams, drive exciting projects forward and become a leader in implementing pioneering information communication technology! In addition, you will have the opportunity to:

Lead/Co-Drive one or more key initiatives, often covering Hardware, Software and Services price models, commercial strategies with the goal of enhancing the monetization of our products
Use your strong analytical thinking and experience with data analytics to explore commercial trends for a global product portfolio
Present insights, conclusions, and recommendations to Ericsson leaders to improve the business at a global scale
Challenge status quo based on facts and logical reasoning, along with motivate change with new insights as a way for Ericsson to become more efficient
Manage and report on key activities by engaging people in different parts of the organization, developing your own leadership skills as well as delivering results in time and with quality
Balance multiple tasks in parallel, handling pressure and managing dynamic prioritization
Analyse market trends and finding significant insights to develop
You will bring

Your personal qualities are important for us, and we believe you are curious, innovative and collaborative. You have a motivation to work proactively, open, and dedicated with a keen interest to learn and to broaden experience and passion when bringing your ideas to the table.

In addition, we believe you have:

BSc or MSc in Industrial Engineering & Management, Information Technology, MBA degree or equivalent
The ability to extract insights out of complex information and present them in a simplified way
Solid presentation skills in English language, with ability to smoothly adapt to the respective audience to convey your message
Comfortable working in MS PowerPoint and MS Excel
Data analysis and visualization skills (for taking a role in Commercial Analytics)
An appetite to work in a fast-paced commercial environment

Be the one who did. Find out more about our Early Career program, what the alumni's are up to now and how the program can transform your career at www.ericsson.com/ecp

Why join Ericsson?

We are a world leader in the constantly evolving environment of communications technology – by providing hardware, software, and services to enable the full value of connectivity. You’ll play a part in using your skills and creativity to push the boundaries of what’s possible. To create never-seen-before solutions to some of the world’s toughest problems.

Join a team of innovators driven to go beyond the norm to build what’s next. At Ericsson, you can be an explorer, a change maker and a force for good.

What happens once you apply?

Click Here to find all you need to know about what our typical hiring process looks like. This role will have its first rotation in Kista Stockholm, Sweden. The selection and interview process is ongoing, so send your application in English as soon as it is ready. For questions or thoughts, reach out to Mathilda Jarl, Recruiter at mathilda.jarl@ericsson.com. Vetting including references and relevant background screening will be conducted for final candidates. We encourage the opportunity to meet you!
