Title: Business Intelligence- och Analytics-konsult - Stockholm
Description:
Hos oss på Capgemini Insights & Data arbetar några av Nordens främsta experter inom Data, Analytics & AI, vilket ger oss bästa möjliga förutsättningar att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas på sin resa mot ett datadrivet beslutsfattande.
Vi bistår våra uppdragsgivare med datadriven affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling hela vägen från strategiska vägval till implementerad lösning och realiserad nytta.
För att möta våra kunders behov söker vi nu dig som vill fortsätta att utvecklas inom främst Microsofts BI stack. För denna roll söker vi personer som har erfarenhet av och kompetenser inom hela Microsofts BI portfölj, dvs allt ifrån SQL Server & Azure till Power Bi. Självklart kan du vara starkare inom något område och/eller ha större intresse för några områden!
Inom Insights & Data är vi ett stort team med specialister och våra tjänster spänner över områden såsom – rådgivning, framtagning av digitala strategier och roadmaps, design och implementation av AI-, IoT-, Analytics- och Data Management-lösningar. Givetvis understött av molnarkitektur och cybersäkerhet. Vår CFO Office-funktion bidrar även med expertis inom finansiell planering, budgetering och prognos samt finansiell konsolidering och koncernrapportering.
Vad vi letar efter:
Vi söker nu dig som har flera års erfarenhet inom Analytics-området och som vill fortsätta utvecklas antingen mot bredare roller eller mot att bli mer specialiserad. Du har beprövad erfarenhet av att jobba med hela Microsofts BI-portfölj och du har även ett driv och intresse för att kommunicera möjligheterna med dessa produkter & tjänster till våra kunder. Du kommer att vara en nyckelspelare i projektens alla faser; från affärs- och dataförståelse till produktionssatta lösningar.
För att bli framgångsrik i denna roll har du tidigare erfarenhet ifrån att ha implementerat BI-lösningar och Self Service-lösningar. Som person är du driven, verksamhetsorienterad och du trivs lika bra med att arbeta självständigt som i grupp. Du sätter stort fokus på dialogen med kund men är även intresserad av att engagera dig i att utveckla oss till att bli en ännu bättre arbetsplats.
Vi tror dessutom att du har:
Gedigna kunskaper inom SQL och DAX.
Flera års erfarenhet ifrån arbete med produkterna inom Azure & SQL Server.
Erfarenhet ifrån arbete med Databricks, Snowflake & Python är önskvärt men inget krav.
Det är viktigt att du är analytisk, lösningsorienterad och nyfiken, att du har en god samarbetsförmåga samt lätt för att kommunicera. Du har relevant högskoleutbildning och du kan svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift.
Hos oss är medarbetarnas utrymme att utvecklas stort och kulturen präglas av frihet under ansvar. För dig som lockas av att vara med i Sveriges vassaste team inom Data, Analytics och AI, är detta ett jobb med framtidsmöjligheter för dig.

Title: Customer Support Representative
Description:
Who are we?
Stockfiller is a Retail tech startup and we are trying to disrupt the flows of food and beverages. By connecting buyers, suppliers and other partners in our eB2B ecosystem we create value for suppliers, grocery chains, independently owned outlets, wholesalers and transportation companies. Our mission is to:
1. Eliminating non-value adding costs for all parties
2. Enabling suppliers (from local producers to large multinationals) to sell in hard-to-access channels while helping them improve their performance (outlet visibility, data analytics) and at the same time significantly reducing food waste at the point in the value chain where it truly makes a difference!
3. Enabling retailers to effectively control their spend and save time, while giving them access to a wide range of value adding services to improve their revenue, costs and operations
At Stockfiller you will be given a unique opportunity to gain insight and be a part of a fast-paced, fun scale-up environment in a company with phenomenal growth and reach on primarily the Swedish market, but also other European markets. You will get to work together with awesome business developers, passionate developers and amazing clients. On top of this you will get to work with a great team in a dynamic and inclusive environment with fantastic coffee and fun after works – right in the center of Stockholm!
Our proprietary systems are used by thousands of suppliers, stores and restaurants throughout Europe and this is where You come into the picture – developing our relationships with our clients! The position is full-time and based in Stockholm.
The role:
As our new Customer Support Representative you will be at the forefront of building strong, long lasting relationships with our customers by assisting them in their everyday operations. You will be helping, guiding and solving issues for both large and small customers and you will work closely with all areas of the company to ensure issues are resolved in the best possible way and to ensure maximum customer satisfaction. For the right candidate the role will give you ample room to grow
Who are you?
At Stockfiller we don’t believe that time necessarily correlates with competence but we think that you ought to have 1+ year of experience in a customer facing role, preferably within Retail and/or Tech in order to be successful in the role. We might be wrong though so don’t see this as a must-have
Experience in Excel / Google Sheets
A ”Can-do” attitude and willingness to learn
Service-minded
Fluent in Swedish and English
Ready to take on responsibility from day one
You care deeply about the people who use our product
You enjoy working in a challenging, fast-paced environment

Title: Application Manager to SF Studios!
Description:
Job Description
Are you a communicative and analytical person who wants to be part of creating a data-driven way of working at Sweden's leading film studio? If the answer is yes, you will be a great addition to SF Studios as our Application Manager!
About the role:
As an Application Manager, you will be responsible for managing and maintaining the financial systems and business processes to meet the needs of the business. You will act as a bridge between IT and the business and play a key role in developing the financial system architecture and increasing productivity for business users.
Additionally, you will be responsible for monitoring and supporting the roll-out of new functionality, troubleshooting and resolving issues with existing systems, designing, and modifying finance applications to streamline data and reporting processes, and ensuring that business users have the necessary knowledge to work effectively with their applications and tools.
You will also be responsible for effective data management, optimizing and quality-assuring existing reporting and integration flows, and leading the organization's efforts to become more data-driven. Your role will involve working closely with various stakeholders across the organization to understand their needs and develop solutions that meet their requirements. In this role, you will be a key member of the IT team, and your contributions will be essential to the success of the finance department and our organization's goals.
Who you are:
To succeed in this role, we believe you can capture and understand an organization's challenges and develop technical solutions that support simplified ways of working. You like to see concrete results and are as a person very hands-on. Since the work requires contact with stakeholders within SF Studios, we believe that you have good communication skills, both verbally and in writing in Swedish and English, and have the ability to build strong relationships. Furthermore, we believe that you are a solution-oriented person who likes to take on great responsibility and enjoys working both in teams and independently.
We believe you have:
A bachelor's or master’s degree in computer science, information systems or equivalent (additional finance studies is a plus)
Ability to turn strategy into action and translate business demands into user-friendly solutions utilizing cloud technologies
Experience working with transforming finance IT processes and business reporting processes.
Experience working with finance systems and data analytics
Are you the star we are looking for?
If this sounds like a position for you - apply today! We're looking forward to receiving your application. For questions, please contact Siri McGarvey, [email protected]

Title: Konsult inom Business Intelligence
Description:
Vill du fortsätta växa som konsult inom Business Intelligence tillsammans med oss på Business Vision?
Business Vision är helhetsleverantör inom data och analys med kontor i Stockholm och Göteborg. Med vår expertis inom Microsofts ledande dataplattform gör vi det lättare för våra kunder att analysera data och identifiera trender. På Business Vision har vi en varm gemenskap och du har stora möjligheter att forma din egen kompetensutveckling. Vi är stolta över att ha skapat en rolig, utmanande och familjär företagskultur där våra värdeord mod, hjärta och trovärdighet genomsyrar hela verksamheten.
Nu vill vi bli fler i Stockholm och Göteborg och söker därför dig som med nyfikenhet och öppenhet gillar att lösa problem, utvecklas och samarbeta tillsammans med våra härliga kollegor. En Business Intelligence-konsult på Business Vision är involverad i projekt från ax till limpa och i rollen arbetar du nära kravställare/användare där du utvecklar betydande lösningar i form av datahantering, dataanalysering och datavisualisering.
Vi söker dig som:
Har några års erfarenhet inom Business Intelligence samt en relevant akademisk utbildning
Har god kunskap inom något av följande områden: DW, datamodellering, ETL-processen (Microsoft Azure, Azure Data Factory, Function Apps, Logic Apps) eller Power BI
Vill utvecklas inom Azure, Snowflake och/eller Databricks
Har god kunskap i något av följande programmeringsspråk: SQL, Python, Javascript eller C#
Är verksamhetsorienterad och lyhörd
Gillar att anta utmaningar och lösa problem
Vill ta ansvar för din egen kompetensutveckling
Gillar att bygga innovativa och användbara lösningar
För att trivas på Business Vision:
Du är nyfiken, driven och vill alltid fortsätta utvecklas
Du ansvarar för och driver din egen kompetensutveckling
Du strävar efter långsiktiga och öppna relationer
Du är ödmjuk, gillar god gemenskap och antar varje uppdrag med hjärta!
Vi på Business Vision är visionärer och strävar efter att efterleva våra värdeord mod, trovärdighet och hjärta i allt vi gör. Med mod är vi nyfikna, kreativa, drivna och strävar ständigt att hålla oss i teknikens framkant. Med trovärdighet fokuserar vi på och utvecklas inom Microsofts molnbaserade dataplattformar för Data Analytics, IoT och AI. Med hjärta eftersträvar vi ett nära samarbete med kund och hjärta reflekteras i sättet vi kollegor samarbetar och stöttar varandra. Om du vill veta mer hur vi arbetar för att främja worklife balance rekommenderar vi att lära vår HR chef Annelie Bergman bloggpost, här. ‍
PS. Kika in vår Instagram för att få en inblick i hur det är att arbeta hos oss
‍
Varmt välkommen att skicka in din ansökan idag!

Title: Junior Digital Analytics Architect
Description:
We are looking for a Digital Analytics Consultant to offer domain expertise and client support for our UK market. You will work closely with stakeholders and various client-side departments to oversee design, development, and validation of Analytics data for the Google or Adobe Analytics platforms.
This role focuses on the design and implementation of customized analytics and attribution strategies as well as creating training and deployment processes that scale globally. This includes the assessment of user-level data and integration with real-time technologies; formulating testing mechanisms to measure and optimize media performance; and overseeing the execution of recommendations for optimal performance across the wide base of paid and unpaid, online and offline media channels our clients leverage.
Responsibilities include:
Client Facing
Hands on implementation of clients' analytics accounts including properties, user management, dashboards, and reporting
Plan, design and implement data analytics across a portfolio of digital channels and platforms in the Google Analytics 360 suite or Adobe Analytics / Marketing Cloud
Architect client-side "source of truth" such as a Site Analytics and Marketing Intelligence platform or dashboard
Source key customer insights through data and testing to define KPIs and inform our digital campaigns
Establish standard process for client's digital properties to set up, maintain and track data for reach, engagement, performance and other behavior metrics
Translate the result of the attribution model/testing towards action partner with our internal team, to drive value across the Marketing channels being tracked; support diverse stakeholders by generating custom reports according to business needs
Work with developers and product owners to determine appropriate metrics and behavior to track new and existing properties
Nurture client understanding of the importance of building & testing an attribution strategy across media buys; act as a consultative resource to help clients understand what their own testing models should look like
Understand and deploy integrations between analytics platforms and external data from POS systems, advertising networks, CRMs, location-based tracking, and offline paid media - predominantly deterministic, potentially probabilistic models
Business Facing
Project manage account analytics efforts setting company-wide best practices and processes
Drive towards higher effective rate between client value and costs; build efficiencies into repeatable processes and scale globally
Work with the Product team to translate business requirements into new products; Work with Sales team to translate products into outbound opportunities; work with Account Management team to R&D and Commercialize products
Educate Accounts, Sales, and Engineering teams on various analytics software to support fulfillment; train employees and offer platform expertise; define roadmap for long-term Customer Analytics needs
What you bring to it:
3+ years hands-on experience with Google Analytics 360 and Google Tag Manager
Fluent English is required
Installation & Architecture experience with Google Analytics (360), Adobe Analytics, VisualIQ, Convertro, Marketo, Segment, Drupal, Data Studio, C3, Salesforce, Target, Monetate, Optimizely, Google Optimize, Tableau, Looker, and any other analytics & visualization platforms
Able to read/write basic HTML/HTML5 /CSS/JavaScript, other front end languages (Python, NodeJS, PHP, etc.), and ability to query large databases (SQL)
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Management of Information Systems, Math, or Statistics/Economics
Excellent analytic, quantitative and problem solving skills with proven ability to deliver actionable insights
Proficient in computer applications used to manipulate large datasets to analyze, test, validate and report public web usage data
Able to relay technical requirements to engineers for execution of custom code
Experience reading API documentation and understanding the technical requirements for implementation with other platforms
Experience in tag architecture analysis and using tagging platform(s) to execute proper data flow
Ability to explain architecture proposals to non-technical audiences and communicate business value of suggested ideas & plans
Passionate about working in an extremely fast-paced, demanding, and fluid start-up environment as well as a desire to build a company up from an early stage
#LI-BK1
About Media.Monks:
Media.Monks is on a mission to create a new future for this industry. Our vision? Build everything with a belief that changing for good comes from changing who does the work. Yep, that means you. Welcome to the party—one global, cross-cultural collective with a passion for using our skills to create better and a better world. That's how we're able to connect the dots between data, content, digital media, and technology from everywhere we are—a true end-to-end model. Joining the Media.Monks collective means having the opportunity to create award-winning work with some of the most gifted, focused, joyful, talents from all over the world.
At Media.Monks, you'll be joining a highly ambitious company on a global mission to win the decade by changing the industry for good. Partner to 8 of the 10 most innovative companies in the world, Media.Monks works with established as well as up-and-coming global, regional, DTC and B2B brands, helping them own their data and build out customer ecosystems to elicit smart, efficient, high-impact engines for growth. We deliver table stakes quickly, creating cost efficiencies from day one to push up the creative effectiveness of our work with every cycle.
We are an equal-opportunity employer committed to building a respectful and empowering work environment for all people to freely express themselves amongst colleagues who embrace diversity in all respects. Including fresh voices and unique points of view in all aspects of our business not only creates an environment where we can all grow and thrive but also increases our potential to produce work that better represents—and resonates with—the world around us.

Title: Azure Data Architect
Description:
Do you love working with data and feel good about making a genuine human impact? Do you want to develop and refine your skills at one of the world's leading digital innovators?

Avanade is a world-leading provider of innovative solutions based on Microsoft's ecosystem with the goal of enabling our customers to achieve more and be successful in their business. We are growing and are looking for a highly driven and skilled Azure Data Architect to join our Data & AI team. We'll surround you with people who are as passionate about technology and innovation as you are.

Why Avanade? Because theres literally no place like this!

We have two parent companies that give us a strong Microsoft ecosystem with space to be ourselves. People who thrive here are motivated, interested in learning and genuinely have a desire to be the best at what they do. If that sounds like you, then we're the perfect match. You'll have access to the latest technology in the Microsoft ecosystem, partnering with some of the biggest and best companies across the world and some seriously smart people to work with to make career-defining things happen. If you want to get even better at what you do and transform businesses from the inside out, there's no better place. At Avanade Sweden, you get the opportunity to work with the latest technology insocially beneficialprojects. Additionally, we help you reach your full potential so that you grow and develop.

We can offer a position in a great team of diverse backgrounds, skills, and experiences, where you will work with some of the largest organizations and companies in Sweden or internationally. As part of a global company, there are plenty of opportunities to collaborate with and learn from colleagues from all over the world. This collaboration can be both in technical or more social form, Avanade has several programs and employee resource groups dedicated to supporting minority groups (women, LGBT+, BIPOC) and volunteering / corporate citizenships.

About the role

As an Azure Data Architect, you will work with clients to identify, document, and translate their business strategy and requirements into solutions and services that help our clients achieve their business outcomes using analytics. Key to this role is that the individual will be an expert in selecting the optimal architecture and delivery approach that will serve clients' needs with a balance of costs, capability, and risks to achieve the business outcomes. Also, being capable of executing what is planned and delivering with excellence is key to succeed.

Based on the market demand for Data and AI solutions this role is critical for Avanade to create new business opportunities and grow existing clients. This role includes developing client roadmaps, program building, incorporating intelligent processes into existing business process, and solution planning that drives our clients desired business outcomes. The scope of solutions can include, diverse data (including IOT) and advanced analytics capabilities, such as data engineering, data modelling, machine learning, and data interaction and visualization that are all powered by Microsoft Azure technologies. The successful individual will be a long-term trusted advisor to our clients to establish programs and system integration projects targeting business outcomes on a repeatable basis.

Day to day you will:
Translate business requirements to technical solutions leveraging strong business acumen.
Analyze current business practice, processes, and procedures as well as identifying future business opportunities for leveraging Microsoft Azure Data & Analytics PaaS Services.
Develop overall solution plans and strategic vision for data and analytics solutions, providing a comprehensive roadmap for clients' needs.
Provide high-level architectural expertise to sales, project and other analytics teams.
Perform key management and thought leadership role in the areas of advanced data techniques, including data modelling, data access, data integration, data visualization, text mining, data discovery, statistical methods, database design and implementation.
Define and achieve a strategic roadmap for the enterprise; including data modelling, implementation and data management for our enterprise data warehouse and advanced data analytics systems.
Identify risks, assumptions, and develop estimates end-to-end based on solution plans.
Build relationships with Solution Architects and collaborate on promoting solution architectural best practices across the company.
We are looking for someone with:
Ability to explain complex analytical methodologies and concepts in non-technical language.
Demonstrated experience of turning business use case and requirements to technical solutions.
Experience designing and solutioning modern data platforms and solutions.
Proven client experience selecting architecture that serve clients' needs with the balance of costs, capability, and risk to meet clients' business objectives.
Strong understanding of the value proposition(s) associated with AI, Data, PaaS and DevOps.
Exceptional written and verbal communication and presentation skills.
Leadership and teamworking skills.
These qualifications will help you stand out:
Ability to conduct data profiling, cataloging, and mapping for technical design and construction of technical data flows.
Experience successfully solutioning digital analytics programs and system integration projects across multiple work streams and geographically dispersed teams.
Knowledge of master data management (MDM) and data quality tools and processes.
Knowledge of DevOps processes (including CI/CD) and Infrastructure as code fundamentals.
Experience designing solutions incorporating AI and advanced analytics.
Experience with data visualization using Power BI, SAS VA, Power Pivot and Tabular models (DAX).
Experience with ETL tools, Databricks, SQL, SSAS and T-SQL.
Working with different project execution methodologies (e.g.Agile).
Experience partnering on analytics-related sales pursuits.
Having experience in one or more of these technologies would be an advantage: Python, .NET, C#, R or Scala.
Even though we have a flexible working remote policy, we expect you to be based in Sweden. Most of our clients are based in Stockholm or Gothenburg, so we expect you to visit them as they request to provide excelent consultancy services.

Did you get interested? Apply today!

Please contact [1] Lubomir Kotzev, lubomir.kotzev@avanade.com, or [2] Laura Matero, laura.matero@avanade.com, if you have any questions.

Title: Software Application Developer
Description:
At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.
Jeppesen, a subsidiary of The Boeing Company, is one of the largest software development companies in Gothenburg. We develop and implement innovative resource management and optimization solutions for the world’s leading airlines. We are dedicated to continuous improvement, delivering more value to our clients, and exploring emerging technologies such as quantum computing, AI and big data analytics.
At Jeppesen’s office in central Gothenburg you will work in a one-of-a-kind software development organization with solutions that make a real difference to people around the world. You will be working in an agile learning organization, surrounded by a team of talented, creative and dedicated colleagues. You will learn and broaden your perspective by working with 400 professionals from more than 30 different nations, but also be part of a global organization allowing for collaboration with customers and colleagues across the world. Most importantly, you will be expected to make a difference.
Jeppesen is looking for Software Application Developer based in Gothenburg, Sweden.
About the position
The Digital Solutions & Analytics implementation department is responsible for the configuration and delivery of our Crew and Ops management products to airline customers and to make sure that we deliver solutions that our customers truly need and that creates value in their organization. This is an opportunity to be part of a skilled team of specialists that solve some of the most challenging optimization problems in the world, value diversity and learn from each other.
As a Software Application Developer you will:
work closely with our clients and other departments to configure the solutions for our clients business needs
deal with technical challenges and programing tasks as well as handling client expectations and building long-term customer relations
We are looking for team members with expertise in software development and user experience as well as showing strong communication and co-operation skills. Interest and expertise in solving problems and being solution oriented is highly valuable in the role. For this position it is vital that you are passionate about learning the airline business and that you see yourself contributing in teamwork, workshops and communicating with different stakeholders as part of the requirements gathering and implementation process.
Required qualifications
Ability to speak and write English fluently
Airline Crew Management and Jeppesen Crew product customization experience
Preferred qualifications:
MSc or BSc in Computer Science / Physics Engineering / Industrial Engineering or equivalent Programing experience
Python, Shell scripting
Experience working within an agile team
Experience from facing end users to enable configuration of software.
Ability to speak additional languages fluently

Join us if you want to:
Professional skills development with our virtual learning tools and platforms (Digital Campus, LinkedIn Learning, Degreed, EdX, Enterprise Mentoring, Communities of Excellence & Practice)
Broaden your experience in international projects, technical workshops and hackathons
Additional days off for Christmas break (December 24th-January 1st)
Employee recognition program (Boeing PridePoints)
Private Medical Insurance (Skandia)
Pension Plan (Defined Contribution Plan)
We put great emphasis on your personal characteristics. We value individuals who have an analytical approach to problem solving, strong communication skills both within and outside your team, an interest for technology as well as human relations and a curiosity to learn and explore new ways of doing things.
Employer is willing to sponsor applicants for employment visa status.
Please apply by sending your CV in English.

Relocation:
This position offers relocation for eligible candidates.

Export Control Requirements: Not an export control position

Equal Opportunity Employer:
We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not accept unlawful discrimination in our recruitment or employment practices on any grounds including but not limited to; color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, physical or mental disability, genetic factors, military and veteran status, or other characteristics covered by applicable law.
We have teams in more than 65 countries, and each person plays a role in helping us become one of the world’s most innovative, diverse and inclusive companies. Applicants are encouraged to share with our recruitment team any accommodations required during the recruitment process.

Title: Product Designer
Description:
Nordnet redefined the financial world as the first digital bank in Europe. Now we are about to do it again and the aim is to create the next generation bank, in the cloud. We know that this requires great people, great teams, and great technology. We are designing products of the future and simplifying a slow-moving industry as a fast-moving fintech company.

This is part of the role

We are looking for a product designer who wants to create world-class user experiences and redefine the financial industry. The main responsibility of a Product Designer is designing innovative products and services for Nordnet across digital touchpoints, such as our web and app.

You'll be a part of our Award winning Design team which you will closely collaborate with during our journey of creating Nordnet Design System and one unified Nordnet design experience. You will work closely with Product Design team, Product Owners, scrum teams and business developers to create intuitive and delightful experiences for our customers.

You will tackle all aspects of the design and business building process, often through leading interactive workshops and design sprints to foster innovation, collaboration, and alignment between Product Design & Product teams.

You will be building Design System and maintaining design system libraries together with Product Design team and a group of passionate developers. You spark innovation and enjoy collaborating with the team to ensure Design System growth.

This is you

To succeed in this role, we believe that you take great pride in your work, that you are open minded, curious and continuously want to learn and grow. We think that you are a true problem solver and optimist with great communication skills. You are enjoying collaborating with designers, data analysts as well as developers and product owners. Agile software development process and tools such as Jira
and Confluence is something you are used to.

With strong organisational and time management skills you are structured, able to self manage throughout design process and drive design work, run workshops and conduct presentations directly towards organization and stakeholders. You enjoy working with cross-functional teams and different stakeholders (bringing together design, agile, engineering, business, data analytics, product and domain owners, etc.) hand in hand when delivering designs.

For us it is important that you have a good understanding of UX and interaction design as well as UI design with attention to details. To have a collaborative mindset and that you enjoy design thinking process, user flows and working with wireframes, visual design, design system integration, design usability and design guidelines documentation.

You feel comfortable with designing UIs that visualise data and are always looking for customer insights and data to drive the best UX decisions in your designs, such as qualitative research and A/B testing.

We think that you have around 2-3 years experience of working as a Product Designer.

As a Product Designer, you

Thrive in interaction with your colleagues and stakeholders.
Have experience in building Design Systems as well as using tools such as Figma and Miro to create and share ideas, concept wireframes, prototypes and designs.-Have an interest and want to learn more about platform and usability guidelines such as
Apple’s Human Interface Guidelines for iOS, Google’s Material Design and WCAG.
Have a portfolio showcasing your work.
This is us

Nordnet is a leading pan-Nordic digital platform for savings and investments. Ever since we started over 25 years ago, our purpose has been to democratize savings and investments. Through innovation, simplicity and transparency, we challenge traditional structures, and give private savers access to the same information, tools and services as professionals.
We offer you the opportunity to work in a great team within a friendly Nordic environment with a strong focus on innovation, product development and technology. We are proud of the friendly and humble environment and commit to our goals as a team, sharing the responsibility, success and failure.
We are 800 employees in Stockholm, Oslo, Helsinki and Copenhagen.
Learn more about Nordnet on our corporate site and in our brand movie This is Nordnet, that describes our identity.
Check out our app at: https://apps.apple.com/se/app/nordnet/id345038631 and https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.nordnet&hl=en&gl=US
You can also visit us on: www.nordnet.se, www.nordnet.no, www.nordnet.dk and www.nordnet.fi
Questions & Application
If you have questions, please contact Talent Acquisition Partner, Alva Hellberg, alva.hellberg@nordnet.se
Apply today by using the button below – we will start interviewing immediately.
Please note that we do only accept applications through our recruitment system, hence no email applications will be considered.
We want to inform you that Nordnet conduct credit and background checks on the final candidate.
We look forward to receiving your application!

Title: Risk Specialist – Nasdaq Clearing
Description:
Why Nasdaq
When you work at Nasdaq, you’re working for more open and transparent markets so that more people can access opportunities. Connections can be made, jobs can be created, and communities can thrive. We want all our employees to have access to opportunities, too. That means planning for career growth, ensuring you have the tools you need, and promoting an inclusive culture where we’re all valued for our unique perspectives.

Here, you will work for a global tech leader committed to breaking down barriers to inclusive prosperity. We see technology as a means to free people up to work together more productively and effectively by centralizing data, analytics, and market intelligence.

Here, we’re committed to building a more diverse and inclusive workforce. Not only is it our responsibility to do better, but we also need representative voices to power the fresh thinking that is vital for our business and our clients.
What we offer
Nasdaq Clearing is looking for a Risk Management Specialist to join the Clearing Risk group and Default Management team at the Stockholm office. Nasdaq Clearing is a multi-asset derivatives clearinghouse covering Commodities, Equity and Fixed Income. The major risks involved in the clearing business are counterparty risk, market risk, liquidity risk and operational risk.
As part of Nasdaq Clearing's first line of defense, the Default Management and Market Risk team is responsible for handling a default of one of the clearing members. The team needs to have robust plans, strategies and tools in place to liquidate the portfolio as swiftly and efficiently as possible.
This role offers an excellent opportunity to work with one of the critical risk mitigating processes in the Nasdaq Clearing and gain insights to capital markets from a clearing and trading point of view. You will also be able to gain knowledge about the risks inherit to derivatives and market regulation. You will work closely with specialists in the Market Risk team, but also other teams in the Risk Management department (Risk Modelling, Credit Risk), Business Development, Operations, Technology and Legal from time to time.
What you will do
In this role, you will be reporting to the Head of Default Management and work closely with the Market Risk team in efforts related to Default Management and Recovery. You will:
Manage and drive enhancement and change initiatives related to default management and recovery
Assist in the execution of close-out/liquidation procedures
Assist in planning and conducing default management exercises across all asset classes
Conduct quantitative and qualitative risk assessments related to market and counterparty risk
Contribute to development of IT business requirements for new default management tools and testing hereof
Contribute to the development and documentation of Nasdaq Clearing´s Default Management and Recovery framework
What We Expect
Master’s Degree in Finance/Mathematics/Engineering or similar
2-5 years of relevant risk management experience (market or counterparty risk)
A solid interest in financial markets, and the ability and willingness to reach a deep understanding of derivatives, clearing and the default management process
Excellent communication and language skills in written and spoken English
MS Office proficient
The ability to remain calm in a stressful environment
What Would Be Useful If You Have
Experience from working in a trading environment
Experience from derivatives clearing
Knowledge of relevant regulatory frameworks (e.g. EMIR)
SQL, Python and MS Power BI programming skills
At Nasdaq, we strive to challenge the status quo and always look for new ways to do things to improve and exceed the collective goals of our teams, company, and customers. A strong inner drive and adaptability are therefore crucial to succeed at Nasdaq.
This is a full-time position located in Stockholm, Sweden. As the process is ongoing, please submit your application in English as soon as possible.

Does This Sound Like You?
At Nasdaq, we provide our employees with the resources and opportunities they need to chart a career of achievement along with a strong compensation package that includes annual bonus opportunity, equity grants, as well as an employee stock purchase program. Nasdaq Sweden provides its employees 32 days of annual vacation (plus 1 additional flex day every two months), health insurance, career development programs, and more. We advocate flexible ways of working and have a hybrid work model.
Come as You Are
Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

Title: Data Architect
Description:
Are you a passionate Data Architect that wants to take Dustin Data & BI platform to the next level?
About the Role: You will be a part of the Enterprise Architecture Team responsible for making sure that we have scalable and flexible data platform that can be used for data analytics and Business Intelligence. We are striving for having information from Dustin’s core domains streaming into the data-platform and landing in a data area per domain.
The role means that you collaborate and work together with colleagues from IT and business. You will be working both on the strategy level and tactical level when making the solution architecture go from hypothesis to implemented. Our current stack is focused on Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory and Databricks. and we are transforming from different stacks into a cloud only stack.
In the long term strategy, Dustin wants to move to a self-servicing data & BI platform where the data is available for different purpose and zones in an easy way. The responsibility of the architect also consists of understanding domain teams need of data-analytics, BI-reporting needs and impact when a domain is changing. Since Dustin is on a journey to be more data-driven Dustin is also starting to set up a scalable machine learning solution and you will be part of that also.
You will be joining at an exciting time when Dustin is expanding in new markets and increasing investments in IT to make sure that Dustin are ready for the future. We are therefore changing our IT-platform and way of work to be more agile and have even closer cooperation with our business.
What you get
Opportunity to make a difference to Dustin success to get data-driven.
Opportunity to set architecture solution for the data and BI-platform.
Working with other architects and together with the Data Innovation and BI-team Dustin.
Flexible working - we work from where we are the most effective.
Collective agreements and wellness grants are examples of benefits.
What you have
Experience from data architecture role focused on Azure and the data-lake components.
Knowledge on of designing solution architecture for a data warehouse in Azure
Experience on machine learning products/frameworks.
Problem solving mindset.
Good presentation, organizational and communication skills with fluency in English.
Recruitment Process

We want a good match! If needed, we will perform multiple interviews, and possibly a case study test. If you have any questions regarding the position, please contact the recruiter, Karishma Sindhu by email at karishma.sindhu@dustin.se or recruiting manager for this role daniel.lundgren@dustin.se at the Enterprise Architecture Team at Dustin.
We will screen and evaluate candidates on an ongoing basis, and close the job ad when we have found the right person for the role. We encourage you to send your motivated application and resume in English as soon as possible.

Title: Consultant/Experienced consultant
Description:
Deloitte is a leading global provider of audit and assurance, consulting, financial advisory, risk advisory, tax, and related services. During its 175-year history, our organization has grown tremendously in both scale and capabilities. Deloitte currently has approximately 415,000 people in more than 150 countries and territories, and serves four out of five Fortune Global 500® companies. Yet, our shared culture and mission—to make an impact that matters—remains unchanged. This is evident not only in Deloitte’s work for clients, but also in our WorldClass ambition, our WorldClimate initiative and our ALL IN diversity and inclusion strategy.
Do you want to make a difference in a dynamic and involving environment built on high professionalism, collaboration, curiosity and high ambitions? We create the framework for a steep learning curve, a strong professional and international network, as well as ensuring that your passion and expertise are expressed in your position.

Over the past few years, Deloitte has built up a significant global assurance department and we are now fully committed to Sweden and the Nordic Region. In Sweden we are now a team of 6 full-time resources and we are growing fast. Do you want to join a newly-established department in Deloitte and deliver valuable projects to our customers in Sweden and Scandinavia? Then Accounting Operations might be a good fit for you!

Who we are

Accounting Operations is an in-audit consulting department that provides a range of services with the ambition to be the CFO’s preferred consultant!

Your team and the assignments

You will become part of the Accounting Operations team focusing on assisting companies in improving their financial closing processes, related financial processes, and internal controls over financial reporting, by applying leading practice knowledge, technology and data analytics. This will give you the opportunity to make positive difference and build relationships with Sweden’s most interesting companies, which will provide great exposure and basis for professional and personal development. As this is a newly-established department, you will have a great opportunity to be part of shaping your own role, explore your entrepreneurial spirit and help build a new and exciting area. You will participate in projects where you will apply your general knowledge within financial processes and/or data analytics and the Deloitte Toolkit to support and advise clients financial departments.

Who we are looking for
Completed Bachelor's or Master's degree in business informatics, finance, accounting, or other science or business degree(s).
1-4 years’ experience either from working as an auditor, in advisory or as a business controller.
Experienced users of Excel, analytics and passion for technology.
Professional experience within finance/controlling or within a Big 4 company or a consulting firm of e.g. SQL, data visualisation tools such as Tableau, QlikView/QlikSense is considered an asset. Experience of Workiva is meritorious but not a requirement.
Ability to communicate accurately and efficiently in English in written and spoken form. Fluency in Swedish is considered meritorious.
You are a person who likes challenges, and is trustworthy as a person. You are innovative, with a problem-solving mindset and have a strong drive to develop yourself and your surroundings.
Deloitte is a multicultural organization where different backgrounds, experiences and skills of individual employees are considered as an asset.

How you’ll grow

Deloitte recognizes that our success in is due to our talented people. We invest heavily in our practitioners providing them with the right tools, training and working flexibility to enable them to deliver and be successful in a motivating and rewarding environment. Teamwork is an important aspect of our success and something we emphasize by bringing our practitioners together on a regular basis to share experiences, knowledge and build strong internal relationships. In addition, we offer:
Access to one of the world's largest consulting organizations, world-class training programs and a powerful network of experienced colleagues
The freedom and opportunity to develop yourself and our business
A pleasant work environment with team-oriented colleagues
Competitive pay and good benefits

Application

You apply online. Your application should consist of a CV and a short cover letter. We process applications and arrange interviews continually. Please apply sooner than later.

As a qualitative part of Deloitte's recruitment process, our final candidates undergo a background check, to increase awareness of our future employees, secure the working environment for our employees and meet regulatory requirements. The background check process is carried out in collaboration with ToFindOut. https://tofindout.se/en/background-check/

Questions

For questions regarding the role welcome to contact Peter Norén at Assurance and Financial Reporting, pnoren@deloitte.se . For questions regarding the recruitment process please contact Rasmus Öhman rohman@deloitte.se .

We look forward to your application!

What impact will you make?

Every day, your work will make an impact that matters, while you thrive in a dynamic culture of inclusion, collaboration and high performance. We do not just aspire to make solutions. We wish to create an impact that makes a positive and crucial difference for the people around our clients, our society and us. Deloitte is where you’ll find unlimited opportunities to succeed and realize your full potential.

Title: Internship - Corporate Governance - Custom Research Analyst – ISS-NIS
Description:
Let’s be #BrilliantTogether
ISS empowers investors and companies to build for long-term and sustainable growth by providing high-quality data, analytics, and insight. We are committed to positively impacting the environment and society through our market-leading solutions and leading by example. Our clients have long turned to ISS to apply their corporate governance views, identify environmental, social, and governance risks, and manage their global proxy voting needs.
Need a refresher on what Corporate Governance and Proxy Voting are?
Corporate governance is the system by which companies are directed and controlled. Boards of directors are responsible for the governance of their companies. The shareholders’ role in governance is developing continuously with investors increasingly acting as responsible stewards and taking into account a wide range of ESG topics. This may include consideration such as the appointment of directors, approving executive remuneration schemes, M&A, and considerations of companies' climate transition plans.
Shareholders are invited by public companies they have shares in to vote on a wide range of topics during annual general meetings. They can delegate their voting power to a representative, who will then be considered a proxy. Here at ISS, we provide the research, insight and recommendations for our client to make informed voting decisions.
Enter the world of corporate governance and responsible investment and jumpstart your career by gaining exposure to the fundamental affairs of businesses and economies on a global scale.
What you will do
ISS Custom Research team, working with high-profile Institutional Shareholders, partners with clients to fully optimize their corporate governance approach through the provision of governance expertise as well as customized deliverables.
The NIS Custom Research Analysts help Nordic clients develop and/or implement customized guidelines that reflect the clients' unique corporate governance philosophy. The NIS team provides clients with customized vote recommendations based on their respective proxy voting guidelines as well as provide customized issue screening and other services.
As part of providing end-to-end management of client policies, the team keeps clients informed of new trends and emerging proposals that have garnered increased interest in the investment community and assists clients in developing and implementing policies on these new issues.
ISS seeks a pool of talented and self-motivated research interns for February 2023. Our interns, guided by our experienced analysts, will be assigned to provide customized vote recommendations to our Nordic clients.
As a Custom Research Intern in the NIS team, you will become an integral part of the team with the crucial role of issuing insightful and well-reasoned proxy vote recommendations and rationale on publicly traded companies, based on client-specific proxy voting guidelines.
This is achieved by gathering and analyzing corporate governance and financial information based the company’s public documents.
You will also answer internal and external queries of the analyses and explaining why a certain vote recommendation was given as well as complete various client-specific projects.
The internship will take place during “proxy voting season.” Our goal is to support our clients in making informed voting decisions on that occasion.
What you can expect from us
Our people are the moving force behind ISS. We are dedicated to hiring the best, most talented people in our industry and empowering them with the resources and support to enhance their health, financial and personal wellbeing. We are committed to fostering, cultivating, and preserving a culture of diversity and inclusion. We are invested in our people and are working every day to ensure a diverse, equitable, and inclusive workplace.
Increase an understanding of relevant technical terminology within the world of corporate governance and responsible investment
Receive in-depth training to fulfill your career aspirations
Expand your know-how and contribute significantly to client work
Make a difference and perform in a workplace of integrity and transparency
This internship is remunerated (26,000 SEK + additional benefits) and will run for 4 months starting in February 2023. Interns are required to be based in the country of employment as of Day 1 of their internship with ISS.
What you will bring to ISS
A relevant bachelor's or master’s degree in economics, business, finance, law, or political sciences or in the process of obtaining such a degree
A prior experience in a relevant area will be considered as an advantage
A strong analytical ability, numeracy, strong oral and written communication skills
The ability to assimilate large quantities of information, work independently and take initiative while also being a team player
An organized and structured mind
Fluent in English (both spoken and written)
A minimum one of the following languages to a native standard:
Danish or Swedish or Norwegian or Finnish
Interested in this great learning opportunity?
Apply online by sending your CV in English along with a one-page cover letter. The cover letter should explain why you are interested in corporate governance, in joining ISS and why you are suitable for the role. Applications without a cover letter won’t be taken into further consideration.
Want to learn more about ISS Corporate Governance?
Visit our website:
https://www.issgovernance.com/about/about-iss/
View additional open roles:
https://www.issgovernance.com/join-the-iss-team/

Title: Azure Data Engineer - Gothenburg
Description:
As an Azure Data Engineer you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards data-driven decision-making. We are all passionate about data!

Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.

Experience from platform modernization
Experience from Tabular cubes and DAX
Databricks
Snowflake
Experience in Snowpro, Matillion or DBT
Data vault modeling
Agile work process

Title: Data Engineer (f/m/d)
Description:
Data Engineer
About the Role
We strongly believe that in this digital age for a sustainable competitiveness it is imperative to have a strong focus on Data & Analytics cutting across Business Services. We are heavily investing in areas like Big Data, Data Science, Reporting, and BI Tools to meet our Digital transformation objectives. We are looking for an experienced professional in the role of Data Engineer to help us in achieving the same. In this role of Data Engineer, you will work across various Data & Analytics Tools, Applications, and Big Data Platforms.
You feel ownership (and are responsible) for the data, as key company asset and driving, govern, and guide teams and know how to maximise value and balance speed and quality in delivery. You are aware about the best practices in Data & Analytics domain and you know the best way to utilise them or you are keen to learn and share your findings with others. As part of the Analytics Microsoft Delivery team you will be working closely with Data Science, Enterprise Architecture, and Business Unit teams to contribute towards the data strategy; as well as with Application Architects and Solution Architects to implement coherent solution architecture and learn from each other.
We’re looking for people who embody our values, aren’t afraid to challenge, innovate, experiment, and move at a fast pace. We’re always looking for ways to improve our products and ourselves. If this is you, we’d love to talk.
What You Will Do
Contribute to delivering business impact and finding and implementing effective solutions in a matrix organisation to drive the enterprise information strategy and analytics transformation
Take a leading role in operationalising data science models to ensure all requirements, including functional, integration, security, performance, quality, and operations are covered
Be responsible for implementing projects and develop, build, configure, unit test, and implement data solutions based on lower level designs within the data infrastructure
Ensure data solution technical functionality and meet requirements outlined in the design in terms of scalability, security, performance, data recovery, reliability, etc.
Align and implement measures to ensure data accuracy and accessibility
Constantly monitor, refine, and report on the performance of data management systems
Implement system configuration changes based on defined solution
Ensure that developed solutions are peer reviewed and formally documented according to company IT standards
Unit test solutions to ensure that they meet quality standards
Maintain, support and repair solutions to ensure performance in accordance with technical and functional specification
Cooperate with other data engineers to make sure that the applications meet requirements and performance goals
Who You Are
University degree in computer science, management information systems, or related discipline
Significant experince of application programming (python or Scala) and ETL/ELT experience
Experience with big data technologies including Hadoop, Apache Spark • More than two years working experience with Databricks and Microsoft Azure Data Lake tools (Azure Data Lake, Azure Databricks, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Warehouse, Power BI, Logic Apps)
More than one year working experience building automation pipelines for testing and deployment using Azure DevOps
Experience working with creating restful APIs and creating external applications to run data science models
Expert in a combination of Spark (Python, R or Scala), PySpark, Spark SQL, Pandas, and/or Spark Streaming
Advanced knowledge of Python to be able to perform code refactoring
Experience in big data tools (Elastic Search/Solr and Kafka) is a plus
Basic understanding of data science
Jupyter Notebooks experience is nice to have

Title: Jobb Service Engineer
Description:
Service Engineer
Alstom
Göteborg
Ansök senast: 2023-04-30
Sök jobbet här
Req ID:409154
What if you could participate in the strategic decisions of a leading mobility company?
Leading societies to a low carbon future, Alstom develops and markets mobility solutions that provide the sustainable foundations for the future of transportation. Our product portfolio ranges from high-speed trains, metros, monorail, trams and e-buses to integrated systems, customised services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility solutions. Joining us means joining a caring, responsible, and innovative company where 75,000 people lead the way to greener and smarter mobility, worldwide.
Join us as a Service Engineer in Gothenburg, Sweden and you will be looking at a career-defining role.
Your mission?
As a Service Engineer, you will mainly be carrying out warranty measures on M33 trams at the depot Slottsskogen in southern Gothenburg. The tasks are varied and include warranty repairs, troubleshooting, modifications and commissioning of M33 trams. Shifts occur and you will work with competent and committed colleagues who will help you get into the work and the team in the best way. There are works in the customer’s other depots (depot Rantorget & depot Majorna).
What your mission includes:
Perform troubleshooting and warranty repairs of M33 trams. Carry out testing and commissioning of vehicles according to instructions. Manage technical surveys. Handle reporting of field data as well as other administration of forms etc. Support maintenance documentation validation. Be up to date regarding changes in maintenance documentation.
Perform modifications according to instruction and drawing documentation in English.
In English , register completed warranty work and root cause analyses in our digital maintenance system Maximo
Your profile?
As a service engineer, it is of great importance that you are driven and have a solid technical interest and ability to solve complex problems. We are looking for you who have experience of technical work from the automation industry, aviation, trains or the like where repair & troubleshooting of mechanical, electrical and digital control systems belongs to your everyday life.
Minimum qualifications:
Graduate in Engineering with a minimum 5 years of technical experience, either mechanical or electrical / electronic engineering
EHS knowledge/exposure
Product knowledge
Data analytics
Fluent in English & Swedish
Ideally:
Railway knowledge
Field Experience
Problem Solving skills
Why Alstom?
Alstom is the leading company in the railway sector, solving the most interesting challenges for tomorrow’s mobility. That’s why we value inquisitive and innovative people who are passionate about working together to reinvent mobility, making it smarter and more sustainable. Day after day, we are building an agile, inclusive and responsible culture, where a diverse group of people are offered opportunities to learn, grow and advance in their careers, with options across functions and geographic locations. Are you ready to join a truly international community of great people on a challenging journey with a tangible impact and purpose?
Alstom is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive working environment where all our employees are encouraged to reach their full potential, and individual differences are valued and respected. All qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by local law.

Title: Principal Optimization Engineer
Description:
Date Posted:
2022-09-09-07:00
Country:
Sweden
Location:
Stenaldersgatan 2 B,213 76 Malmo
Role: Principal Optimization Engineer
Location: Scheelevägen 27, 223 63 Lund, Sweden.
Remotely from anywhere in Europe is also possible.
Contract type: Permanent
Build a career with confidence
At Carrier, you’re joining the world leader in healthy, safe, sustainable and intelligent building and cold chain solutions. We create solutions that matter for people and our planet – and our employees are the heart of it all. We are a company of innovators and problem-solvers who are united by The Carrier Way – our vision, values and culture.
As an employer of choice, we strive to provide a great place to work that attracts, develops and retains the best talent, promotes employee engagement, fosters teamwork and ultimately drives innovation for the benefit of our customers. In short, Carrier’s greatest assets are the expertise, creativity and passion of our employees – and we’re excited for you to join the team.
The Computational Engineering group within Systems & Controls COE (Carrier WHQ) has responsibility for developing and deploying model-based methods and tools for design and operation of Carrier products. This includes using mathematical models for taking product design decisions, quantification of system uncertainty, and securing efficient operation in the field. The core technology areas of the group are large-scale continuous and discrete optimization, variability analysis, data analytics, machine learning, numerical and algorithm analysis, as well as understanding requirements for mathematical models to be reliably used by numerical algorithms.
We are hiring and looking for our next Principal Optimization Engineer
About the role
As a Principal Optimisation Engineer you provide technical leadership in the area of numerical optimization of thermo-fluid systems which are core to the Carrier business – this includes trade-off and optimize energy efficiency, production cost and operating economy.
You engage with global product teams to solicit business needs and convert those into computational decision-making workflows, methods and tools to radically impact how Carrier products are designed, deployed and operated. Key targets include improving engineering effectiveness as well as developing disruptive, innovative methods for model-based design and operation of Carrier systems.
You also take active part in product development to support design engineers in adopting and using new methods and tools.
You also work closely with other teams in Systems & Controls COE, including teams responsible for model development (to drive the development of optimization-friendly thermo-fluid models) and controls engineering (to promote the use of computational optimization strategies (MPC, RTO) as needed).
We are offering you
We are committed to offering competitive benefits programs for all of our employees and enhancing our programs when necessary.
A dynamic and international work environment in a company with high technology products
A strong growth strategy and people who are passionate about what they do.
The ability to work remotely or in office, depending on your location and preference
Requirements
Education:
MEng or PhD in a relevant Engineering discipline (e.g., applied mathematics, mechanical or chemical engineering) with 10+ years of experience
Skills and qualifications:
Proven ability to capture engineering design and operation problems as mathematical programming problems (NLPs), including attention to reliable convergence of such problems.
In-depth knowledge and experience with the mathematical theory (applied mathematics, numerical analysis and functional analysis), algorithmic foundations (notably existence and convergence proofs), and methods/tools for numerical optimization (SQP, interior point method, etc.) of large-scale systems.
Experience from using common algorithms/solvers for large-scale gradient-based non-linear programs, e.g., IPOPT, CONOPT, KNITRO, and WORHP, including their respective applicability to different types of problems. Knowledge about discrete optimization formulations, methods, and algorithms is a merit.
Expertise and experience with physics-based modeling principles and best practices of thermo-fluid systems, such as vapor compression cycles or power plants.
Familiarity and experience with development of computational platforms and tools in Python or equivalent.
Familiarity with using HPC and cloud-based platforms for computation at scale.
Demonstrated ability to lead and work as part of a multidisciplinary team and an entrepreneurial attitude towards technological innovation in a global environment.
Self-starter who is well-organized in an international team environment, and has excellent interpersonal, leadership and communication skills.
Responsibilities
Deployment. Ensure that methods and tools developed in the group impact the Carrier business through engagement in global product projects, including capture and formulation of computational problems arising in such projects.
Methods, tools and algorithms. Ensure that appropriate computational methods, tools and algorithms for large-scale numerical optimization are based on sound mathematical foundations and are deployed to match the needs of the Carrier business, including contributing to the architecture, development, testing and documentation of the methods and tools developed in the group.
Modeling for optimization. Support development of mathematical models for thermo-fluid systems are built based on principles and best practices that secure reliable application of numerical optimization algorithms.
Talent. Support development and training of staff within Carrier product teams and within the Computational Engineering group; contribute to talent pipeline by supervising student internships and theses.
Our commitment to you
Our greatest assets are the expertise, creativity and passion of our employees. We strive to provide a great place to work that attracts, develops and retains the best talent, promotes employee engagement, fosters teamwork and ultimately drives innovation for the benefit of our customers. We strive to create an environment where you feel that you belong, with diversity and inclusion as the engine to growth and innovation. We develop and deploy best-in-class programs and practices, providing enriching career opportunities, listening to employee feedback and always challenging ourselves to do better. This is The Carrier Way.
Join us and make a difference.
Apply Now!
Carrier is An Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or veteran status, age or any other federally protected class.
