Title: Ikano Bank – Data Business Analyst
Description:
Are you passionate about data and information management? Are you a motivated, organized person seeking an exciting and rewarding opening in a fast-paced environment?
Do you have Analyst experience within data and/or financial services industry? If you’re looking for change and ready to make changes – Ikano are looking for you!
About the role
As a Business Analyst for Data Delivery at Ikano, you have a key role in the success of data product deliveries in the bank. You work closely with different business stakeholders to create efficient data solutions. You are responsible for maximizing value delivered by working together with business stakeholders to design data products iteratively and incrementally.
You collaborate with data product owners and data delivery team in understanding and develop features through our Agile Release Trains. You will be creating and expanding our data solutions that will supply the bank with the data that will fuel our digital transformation. The solutions covered ranges from traditional data warehouse solutions for reporting BI to more modern solutions (data lakes and streams) to handle real time reporting and advanced analytics.
Ikano Bank’s Digital organization is on an exciting transformation journey to advance our mindsets, ways of working and solutions. Ikano’s vision is to establish user friendly digital capabilities for the many people by unlocking the full potential of our co-workers and partners.
Key responsibilities
Defining the requirements and features that will create capabilities in line with the overall bank strategy
Creating features with relevant acceptance criteria
Build trust and effective relationships with relevant stakeholders by analyzing their needs and find solutions
Reviewing features to make sure that they are in line with the objectives Preparing documentation and presentations
Support the Data & Analytics product team to create, maintain and prioritize the data product backlog and roadmap
Understand Ikano Bank’s strategic initiatives working closely with Product Management, to deliver products that helps the Bank in achieving the desired objectives
Drive the planning of product releases, communication, learning and set expectation for delivery of new features and functionalities.
Key Qualifications
3-5 years’ experience as an analyst or similar preferably within financial services industry specifically within finance or risk.
You have a passion and drive to work with technologies in a team-oriented environment. You have a basic understanding of the different steps of software development.
Experience and knowledge of Agile frameworks, preferably SAFe Strong analytical and problem-solving skills Excellent English communication skills (written and verbal), including facilitation
You have good technical writing skills with the ability to produce documentation of complex ideas and solutions.
Experience within / knowledge of data, and technical architecture for Data & Analytics
Preferred but not a must is experience in provisioning of data through modern technology
You have Ikano’s values, common sense, simplicity and daring to be different at heart.
We want our customers, partners and co-workers to choose us for what we stand for, what we deliver and how we deliver it. Three basic values guide our work: common sense and simplicity, working together, and daring to be different. These values should feel natural to you. This position is a full-time employment, located in Malmö and you will report to head of Data Delivery.
What Ikano Bank offers you
This is a unique opportunity to join Ikano Bank on an exciting journey delivering awesome services for the many people. As a Business Analyst in the Data Delivery team, you will have a great platform to expand your career and continue to develop your skills. You will work in a diverse and friendly team in a fast-paced environment. Operating at the centre of events, you will have an active role in various decision forums to create a great foundation for further development. This position is more than what meets the eye. You will get the chance to push boundaries and influence your daily work. All as part of a caring and open culture where we live our values, work hard, have fun, and operate with a long-term perspective. Because here opportunities arise, and growth follows.
How to apply
Ikano Bank is partnering up with Academic Search International. For further questions in the process please contact senior consultant Marcus Kleine, marcus.kleine@academicsearch.se or 0736-503177 or Researcher Johanna Ohm, johanna.ohm@academicsearch.se or 0701-653165. All information is handled confidentially in accordance with Academic Search integrity policy as well as the new data protection act, GDPR. This means that we can only process applications coming through the applications system. Thank you for your understanding.
We kindly ask you to submit your application as soon as possible, we may work continuously with the selection and interview process. We look forward to hearing from you!
About Ikano Bank
Ikano Bank creates possibilities for better living by offering simple, fair and affordable services, enabling a healthy economy for the many people. Our offer includes savings and loan products for consumers, sales support services for retailers, and leasing and factoring solutions for businesses. We conduct business in Sweden, Denmark, Finland, Norway, the UK, Poland, Germany and Austria. Ikano Bank is a part of the Ikano Group who owns 51 % of Ikano Bank. Ingka Group, the largest IKEA retailer representing about 90% of IKEA retail sales and operates IKEA sales channels under franchise agreements with Inter IKEA Systems B.V., owns the remaining 49 % of the Bank. Ikano Bank’s head office is located in Malmö, Sweden and the company is registered in Älmhult, Sweden where the business was once founded.
About Academic Search
Academic Search International is one of Scandinavia’s most merited companies within Executive Search & Interim management. Our focus is people with documented manager and specialist competences. We have close collaborations with national and international companies with strong brands and purpose. Our mission is to unite the best qualified candidates with the toughest challenges at the most interesting companies in Sweden. Our values are KNOWLEDGE, ENGAGEMENT, RESPONSIBILITY and COLLABORATION. Through these values, we make a difference in all our relationships. www.academicsearch.se

Title: Campaign Manager
Description:
Patriksson Talent is looking for an experienced Campaign Manager to join our team, working with our portfolio of international Talents in the successful execution of campaigns for brands within the beauty, fashion and lifestyle niche. In the role of campaign manager, you will work in close liaison with both our Talents and the brands they collaborate with in order to secure first class implementation and management of the partnerships and campaigns. You are a strong project manager and you will provide structure for both the internal as well as the external work with our Talents. You work in close dialogue with a Talent Manager to optimize and ensure that each assignment and campaign is carried out with high and consistent quality and you will continuously update sales reports and monitor trends to develop the business area together with Talent Managers and Head of Operations.

Furthermore, you have a keen interest in the industry and are always on the look-out for new Talents, emerging trends and opportunities.
This is a permanent position with a 6-month probation period based in Stockholm. Starting date: March 2023 or earliest possible date.
Main tasks and responsibilities
Responsible for securing the implementation of signed campaign deals for our Talents.
Responsible for structuring, developing and optimizing the business together with Talent Manager and Head of Operations.
Time planning and scheduling of campaigns for Talents including coordination of all parts of each collaboration for Talents.
Ongoing monitoring and final reporting to clients after completed campaigns including data analysis.
Assist Talent Manager and Head of Operations with quotations and budget work.
Create necessary routines, templates and internal/external presentations for meetings.
Responsible for invoicing of the campaigns.
Ongoing close dialogues with Talents for strategic advice and development.
Provide Patriksson Talent's own digital channels with updated material and content.
Serve as an exceptional ambassador for Patriksson Talent and network with key stakeholders in the industry.
External monitoring of talents, collaborations and campaigns.
Qualifications and personal skills
Relevant postgraduate or professional degree.
Specific Talent representation experience is a bonus.
Excellent coordination, project management and administrative skills.
A true team player with strong ability to also work independently.
Proven track record of working with multiple projects at the same time.
Ambitious, proactive and service-oriented approach.
Strong interest in the Creative industries and digital and social media trends.
Developed analytical ability.
Fluent in English & Swedish, both written and oral.
About Patriksson Talent
Patriksson Talent represents a curated pool of influential digital creators that enable brands to tap into desired communities and current cultural codes in social media. We create bespoke collaborations for our Talents that deliver engagement, reach, revenue, and trustworthy consumer relations for ambitious brands across the globe. Combined with our excellence in influencer marketing and data analytics, we optimize each collaboration, securing brand-coherent content, and actionable insights. For more information, visit our website www.patrikssontalent.com.
Rooted in a strong heritage of brand-building and communication, Patriksson Talent is part of Patriksson Group www.patrikssongroup.com and closely linked to strategic communications agency Patriksson with offices in Stockholm, Paris, Copenhagen, and Oslo, as well as the digital influencer platform INC. Society www.incsociety.com.

Title: Game Operations Specialist | Candy Crush Saga
Description:
Craft:
Games Design & Production
Job Description:
As a Game Operations Specialist you will create, launch and monitor events to support the Candy Crush Operations & Analytics org. in Stockholm Sweden. Working with a variety of stakeholders across our different Business Areas, you will have a vital role in delivering events and content to millions of customers worldwide. Critical to your success is an ability to easily adapt to new situations and tight deadlines, strong communication skills and a business mindset.
Role Within Our Kingdom
Reporting to a Director in Operations, you will;
Configure Tests - Compile components to create test and events as required from stakeholder requests.
QA Test - Manual QA test to ensure performance is as intended, both pre and post launch into live environment.
Push content into the Live environment – Push events, live ops, a/b tests into the live environment that will be experienced by millions of customers worldwide.
Monitor & Report – Monitor the live performance of content and tests, flagging for immediate issues and reporting results according to KPIs.
Skills to Create Thrills:
Ability to adapt and learn quickly
Excellent attention to detail and quality orientated
Strong communication and stakeholder management skills
Solid understanding or enthusiasm for the games industry
High analytical & problem- solving skills
Prior experience within QA or Data/Analytics is a plus
About King
King is the game developer behind the world- famous Candy Crush franchise, as well as mobile game hits including Farm Heroes, Bubble Witch and Pet Rescue. Candy Crush is the top- grossing franchise in US app stores, a position it has held for the last two years, and King’s games are being played by 245 million monthly active users as of Q3 2021. King, which is part of the Activision Blizzard group since its acquisition in 2016, employs nearly 2,000 people in game studios in Stockholm, Malmö, London, Barcelona and Berlin, and offices in San Francisco, New York, and Malta.
A Great Saga Needs All Sorts of Heroes
Making games is fun. Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply cannot expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes.
Making the World Playful
Making the World Playful is what inspires us to create new experiences and raise the bar. It’s what makes King a place where we can all dream bigger, continue to add innovation to our games, broadening the portfolio and exploring new territories in mid- core and casual. We take the art and science of gaming to the next level through our curiosity for the unexplored, passion for games, respect for each other and love for our players - and we’re not afraid to have fun along the way. In fact, together with our parent company Activision Blizzard and experts around the world, we believe having fun is good for you. There has never been a better time to join us. We're dreaming bigger and see a world of possibilities ahead. If you share our passion, our values, and our hunger to shape the future, join us in Making the World Playful!
Applications need to be in English.
Discover King at careers.king.com

Title: BI-Developer
Description:
Nordiska Kreditmarknadsaktiebolaget är ett kreditmarknadsbolag med kontor i centrala Stockholm, Sundsvall och Oslo. Vi erbjuder sparande och lån för att möjliggöra våra kunders affärer. Samtidigt erbjuder vi våra partners att skapa egna finansiella erbjudanden gentemot sina kunder med hjälp av våra molnbaserade tjänster och APIer. En stark entreprenörsanda i kombination med djup kunskap om finansteknikutvecklingen ger oss god förståelse för hur man navigerar och presterar i den starkt växande fintech-sektorn. Vi överbryggar klyftan mellan den nya och den gamla bankeran genom att erbjuda tekniskt avancerade lösningar och finansiering där efterfrågan ökar.

BI-Developer

Vi erbjuder
Hos oss får du möjligheten att vara en del av en positiv och engagerad gemenskap där allas bidrag är viktigt för vår tillväxt och framgång. Som en del av Nordiska får man de förutsättningar och det stöd man behöver för att kunna utvecklas inom sitt eget kompetensområde, men även möjligheten att lära sig andra delar av verksamheten för att kunna vidareutvecklas inom bolaget. Vi erbjuder en snabbrörlig, öppen och motiverande arbetsplats med kompetenta kollegor, där alla hjälps åt för att nå våra mål tillsammans.

Om rollen
Som Business Intelligence Developer (”BI-Developer”) hos Nordiska så kommer du vara del av ett Data Analytics team som arbetar med den senaste tekniken i en molnbaserad miljö. Du kommer att spela en betydande roll i arbetet med utveckling av beslutsstödslösningar för intern kontroll av risker och automation av finansiella rapporter. Vidare, kommer du tillsammans och med stöd från ditt team, arbeta med att översätta affärs- och verksamhetskrav från interna stakeholders till rapporter, tabeller och visuella objekt i våra BI-verktyg.

Din profil
Du är en person som känner stor passion samt nyfikenhet för data och teknik. Att arbeta i ett snabbrörligt team med stort ansvar är något som både passar och motiverar dig. Du är trygg i din kompetens och de uppgifter du ansvarar för, genomför du med ett stort driv och struktur.
Du har erfarenhet och förståelse för modellering i BI-verktyg och stimuleras av att lösa problem med hjälp av data. Utöver detta ser vi att du har god analytisk förmåga och enkelt kan omsätta verksamhetskrav till datadrivna lösningar. I övrigt så vill vi att du har erfarenhet från arbete med SQL och förståelse för arbete kring datalager, datamodellering och dataintegration.

Vi söker dig med
Minst 2 års erfarenhet av arbete som Business Intelligence Developer eller liknande
Mycket goda färdigheter i SQL och erfarenhet av att arbeta med stora datamängder
IT-, ekonomi- eller ingenjörsutbildning på kandidatnivå eller motsvarande
Övergripande kunskap och förståelse för olika typer av data warehouse-lösningar
Erfarenhet från att arbete i molnbaserade miljöer
Flytande i tal och skrift på svenska samt engelska

Meriterande
Erfarenhet från Finans-/Fintech-branschen
Erfarenhet av att arbeta med hela kedjan från utveckling, test och produktionssättning (CI/CD)
Erfarenhet av arbete i Snowflake och med verktyg såsom DBT
Erfarenhet från att arbeta i Python
Arbetat i Power BI

Allra viktigast är att du och vi på Nordiska kan bli en bra match. Vi har en utmanande och spännande resa framför oss - om du vill vara med - här är din chans!
Vi finns i centralt belägna lokaler och vårt arbete bedrivs både på kontoret och flexibelt på distans. Bolaget har idag ca 65 medarbetare i Stockholm, Sundsvall och Oslo. Läs mer om oss på www.nordiska.se

Ansökan
För frågor och mer information så är du varmt välkommen att kontakta Filip Björnsjö, Data Scientist, på +46 (0) 73 543 22 44 eller filip.bjornsjo@nordiska.com

Title: Business Intelligence
Description:
Sopra Steria fortsätter att växa och därför söker vi nu fler nya kollegor till vår enhet Data & Analytics. Arbetar du med Business Intelligence, BI, Data Warehousing, Data Engineering, Beslutsstöd, Analytics, Data Science, Machine learning – för oss är inte det viktiga vad du kallar det utan att du brinner för att hjälpa kunder att skapa värde genom digitalisering. Vi erbjuder en av Sveriges bästa arbetsplatser (enligt Great Place to Work) och har av Gartner rankats till topp fem bolag inom digital transformation. Nu söker vi dig som vill jobba som konsult och vill fortsätta att växa tillsammans med oss.
Vi vågar lova dig en omväxlande vardag och otroliga kollegor, på en arbetsplats där trivsel är en strategisk prioritering. Vi tror på Power of Sharing och arbetar ständigt med att dela med oss av våra kunskaper till varandra och till samhället i stort.
Om tjänsten
I vårt Data & Analytics-team har vi gedigen erfarenhet av att hjälpa våra kunder utveckla och underhålla beslutsstödslösningar på högsta nivå. Vi erbjuder möjligheten att kombinera arbete i något av våra många utmanande uppdrag med vidareutbildning och certifieringar inom området. Vi levererar både i projekt och som helhetsåtagande och arbetar helst tillsammans i team. Vi använder våra sammantagna kompetenser och förmågor till att skapa värde åt våra kunder utifrån deras data. På Sopra Steria ger vi dig verktygen och förutsättningarna för att fortsätta växa i din yrkesroll. Det är så vi jobbar.

Vi är partner med flera stora aktörer inom BI-området, till exempel Microsoft, Oracle, Peltarion och Qlik.
Vi tänker oss att tjänsten i första hand är en anställning vid något av våra fina kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö eller Östersund men i dessa digitala tider kan det även vara aktuellt på andra orter i landet.
Vem är du?
Till den här rollen söker vi dig som har flera års erfarenhet av att jobba med modellering, hantering, lagring och presentation av data. Med din erfarenhet vet du vad som krävs och vi gissar att du är van att hantera till exempel SQL Server, Azure, Redshift, Power BI, Qlik, Quicksight eller Tableau.
Är du nyutexad? Missa inte att kolla in vårat accelerateprogram, utsett till Sveriges bästa inom IT! Accelerate-program | Sopra Steria
I övrigt söker vi dig som:
Gillar att jobba med ny teknik.
Delar med dig av kunskap till dina kollegor.
Är nyfiken och vill utvecklas. På riktigt.
Behärskar svenska och engelska väl i både tal och skrift.
Vilka är vi?
Vi är 47 000 kollegor i 30 länder som är experter inom IT och management. Sopra Steria har blivit utsedda till en av Sveriges bästa arbetsplatser, Karriärföretag 2022 och av Gartner som ett topp 5 bolag inom digital transformation. Tillsammans skapar vi förändring på riktigt genom digitalisering för några av världens främsta bolag inom både privat och offentlig sektor.
Ansökan
Nu vill vi gärna höra lite om dig! Ansök enkelt genom att antingen ladda upp ditt CV eller länka direkt till ditt LinkedIn-konto via annonsen på vår hemsida! Om det fortfarande finns något du funderar över är du välkommen att kontakta Sanna Salén, sanna.salen@soprasteria.com eller Anna Sandell, anna.sandell@soprasteria.com
Vi jobbar löpande med urval och intervjuer, skicka därför gärna in din ansökan så snart som möjligt.
Vi ser fram emot att få höra ifrån dig!

Title: ESG Client Relations Manager [Nordics and Dutch Markets]
Description:
ESG solutions enable investors to develop and integrate responsible investing policies and practices, engage on responsible investment issues, and monitor portfolio company practices through screening solutions. It also provides climate data, analytics, and advisory services to help financial market participants understand, measure, and act on climate-related risks across all asset classes. In addition, ESG solutions cover corporate and country ESG research and ratings enabling its clients to identify material social and environmental risks and opportunities.
OVERVIEW
ISS ESG is looking for an individual who is enthusiastic about the impact of environment, social, and governance (ESG) data and research on the institutional investor community, and who wants to work with these clients to support sustainable investing.
As a member of the Nordic and Dutch ESG Client Success team, your focus will be on clients who subscribe to ISS’ leading ESG data and research solutions. You will help and support senior members of the team and over time take responsibility of your own clients.

The position is in ISS ESGs’ Stockholm office in Sweden, which is based central. Our hybrid working structure means 3 days in office and 2 days remote.

What we are looking for:
Strong interest in working with ESG data, research and client questions, and interest in working in the finance industry with institutional investors (Asset Owners and Asset Managers)
Passion to make a sustainable difference in the investment world
Team players with a collaborative mindset and positive, can-do attitude
Fluency in English and a Nordic language or Dutch
Strong project & time management / organizational / multi-tasking skills
Experience or strong interest in client facing roles and ability to understand key client needs

Our hybrid working structure means 3 days in office and 2 days remote. Our offices are based in central Stockholm

RESPONSIBILITIES
Act as an ESG support to internal and external stakeholders,
Proactively develop and strengthen relationships with ISS ESG clients to help them understand best practice use cases, data methodology, delivery and data management.
Support senior ESG specialists with onboarding, platform management and know-how.
Oversee new client on-boarding and lead project management of client-related deliveries
Work cross-functionally with other ISS teams (operations, research, sales, development, product, etc.) to successfully meet client needs
Perform client training on ISS platforms to optimize their user experience
Track the overall health of the client relationship, including the updating of internal client data systems to track key elements of the relationship and service delivery. Create and implement client action plans.
Contribute to, and collaborate with, internal initiatives to support the growth within the ESG business
Stay abreast of key market trends to better advise clients and understand emerging use cases for data.
Become a ESG specialist with subject matter expertise on ISS ESGs’ research and solutions, including ESG Ratings, Controversy and Sector Screening, SDGs, Climate Research, Sustainable Finance Regulatory Solutions

QUALIFICATIONS
Bachelor’s degree; Master’s degree is preferred
Ability to analyze key client needs, with a commercial orientation that helps identify sales opportunities
Ability to quickly learn and adapt to new content, and learn new ESG products
Project management/organizational/multi-tasking skills
Outstanding writing, communication and presentation skills
Proficient in Excel and Power Point
English and a Nordic language or Dutch
Understanding of institutional financial market participants (Asset managers, Asset owners)

The Swedish Confederation of Professional Associations (SACO) is a politically independent central organization for 22 unions comprising university graduates in Sweden. You are welcome to contact the local representatives of SACO at ISS-Ethix on
SACO@iss-esg.com
. However, note that no applications sent to this e-mail address will be accepted.

Title: Data Coach inom Data Management Office på Handelsbanken
Description:
Är du en person som brinner för att skapa värde från data/information? Vågar du tänka i nya banor och utmana gamla tankesätt? Sök då rollen som Data Coach hos oss.
Handelsbanken är en stabil arbetsgivare med generöst förmånspaket och det finns stora möjligheter att göra karriär inom organisationen. Tjänsten är placerad på vårt kontor i centrala Stockholm, och området applicerar flexibelt arbetsliv vilket ger dig möjlighet att kombinera hemarbete med arbete på kontoret utifrån verksamhetens behov.
Om tjänsten och rollen
I rollen som Data Coach agerar du förändringsledare och katalysator för att bidra till verksamhetens förflyttning och datamognad.
Vår uppgift är att stötta och leda Handelsbanken i förflyttningen att bli ”data-driven”, men också ”data-informed”. Det betyder att bankens olika funktioner ska förstå och praktiskt använda dataunderbyggd information som verktyg i den löpande verksamheten och i utvecklingen av effektiva, kvalitativa och säkra produkter och kundupplevelser som ligger i linje med bankens strategi och mål.
I rollen kommer du bland annat att:
Medverka i facilitering av verksamhetens arbete i sina olika processer för att hjälpa till att identifiera vilken data, verktyg och kompetens som behövs för att realisera strategiska mål för bankens olika affärsområden
Koordinera olika verksamhetsbehov (use case) som ingår i bankens Data & Analytics-portfölj och medverka till att utveckla best-practice kultur och arbetssätt
Utvärdera behov, coacha och utveckla team eller individer för att bygga upp en djupare och bredare kompetens runt data- och analysområdet.
Samordna i organisationen och fungera som brygga runt datarelaterade frågor och begrepp, samt koppla ihop rätt kompetenser vid behov.
Du kommer delta i en spännande förändringsresa som styr banken mot modernare dataarkitektur och teknologier, nya tjänster och etablering av en gemensam datakultur. Vår avdelning är relativt ny och utvecklas löpande. Det ger dig möjlighet att vara med och forma den verksamhet som vi bedriver för att uppfylla både vårt uppdrag, men även hur din roll kommer att se ut i framtiden.
Dina kompetenser och personliga egenskaper
Vi söker en person som är lyhörd, självgående och driven lagspelare med egen prioriteringsförmåga. Som person drivs du av att utvecklas, är positivt engagerad, nyfiken och flexibel. Du har ett genuint intresse för att coacha och utveckla människor och att skapa förutsättningar för att alla medarbetare ska bidra till sin fulla potential. Du är även strukturerad, metodisk och lösningsorienterad.
Vi ser att du har en IT/teknisk-utbildning eller motsvarande kunskaper som du fått genom tidigare arbete. Du behöver ha goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska, både i tal och skrift.
Ytterligare kompetenskrav:
erfarenhet av arbete med data- eller informationshantering - från sälj, produktutveckling eller IT-organisation.
erfarenhet av förändringsarbete och/eller leda projekt, test- eller kravarbete. Vi ser att du kan tolka och omsätta verksamhetsbehov till välformulerade och värdeskapande use case.
ska kunna föra dialoger, argumentera och paketera budskap på ett inspirerande vis för olika roller inom hela Handelsbanken.
erfarenhet från arbete i agila miljöer.
Det är meriterande med erfarenhet av att etablera och driva utbildningsprogram samt utveckla informations- och utbildningsmaterial. Erfarenhet från finansbranschen är också meriterande.
Vi erbjuder
Trygg arbetsgivare
Spännande och utmanande arbetsuppgifter
Work-life balance
Utvecklingsmöjligheter
Hybridarbete
Sunda värderingar kring samhällsansvar och hållbarhet
Hälsa och friskvård
Tjänstepension och försäkring
Personal-, lunch- och föräldraförmåner samt rådgivning
Självklart vet vi att du är unik med dina erfarenheter samt dina personliga egenskaper och vi ser fram emot att höra vad du kan bidra med i denna roll. Urval och intervjuer sker löpande och tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas före sista ansökningsdatum. Välkommen med din ansökan.
Om oss
Med över 2000 medarbetare är vi en av Sveriges största tech-organisationer. Vi tror på framtiden, lika mycket som vi är stolt över vår historia. Därför är vi ständigt på jakt efter nya förmågor som ser utmaningar och möjligheter i vårt digitaliseringsarbete. Det gäller allt från drift, underhåll och systemförvaltning till utveckling, innovation och design. Vi är en decentraliserad organisation där du som medarbetare får ett stort eget ansvar. Långsiktiga affärsrelationer, lågt risktagande och kostnadsmedvetenhet är hörnstenar i Handelsbankens företagskultur och lägger grunden för att vår verksamhet bedrivs på ett ansvarsfullt, hållbart och framgångsrikt sätt. När vi rekryterar nya medarbetare söker vi efter personer som delar bankens grundläggande värderingar. Målet är att våra medarbetare ska spegla den marknad som vi verkar i – med olika bakgrund, kompetens och arbetslivserfarenhet samt olika sätt att tänka och lösa problem.
Jobbtyp: Heltid

Title: Commercial Application Specialist Anesthesia/Perioperative and Critical Care
Description:
Job Description Summary
In the role of commercial application specialist in Anesthesia/Perioperative and Critical Care, you will mainly work in Sweden to support the Swedish market, in addition you will also be supporting Norway and Denmark when needed. Your base will be in the Danderyd office and you are reporting to the Swedish Country Sales Manager, Patient Care Solutions.
Job Description
GE Healthcare is a leading global medical technology and digital solutions innovator with over 100 years of healthcare industry experience and around 50,000 employees globally. We enable clinicians to make faster, more informed decisions through intelligent devices, data analytics, applications and services, supported by our Edison intelligence platform. We operate at the center of an ecosystem working toward precision health - digitizing healthcare, helping drive productivity and improving outcomes for patients, providers, health systems and researchers around the world.
GE Healthcare Swedish HQ is located in Danderyd, Stockholm.
As Commercial Application specialist, you will promote GE Healthcare’s Anesthesia/Perioperative and Critical Care solutions portfolio including Anesthesia Workstations and Patient Monitoring, both internally and externally to drive commercial success and ensure total customer satisfaction. You will be responsible for pre-sales demo of our products and solutions, promoting unique selling points and clinical benefits, as well as post-sales customer application support, including on-site clinical commissioning and support during go-live. You will also coordinate and execute formal training courses at the designated customer installation site. You will work in close collaboration with the Account Managers, being a key contributor in driving the sales of GE Healthcare products to the medical community in Sweden.

In addition to your role in the sales organization, you are part of the Swedish education organization, GE Healthcare Academy. The training organization today consists of about 50 employees and together we provide more than 900 customer training days per year, we offer more than 70 courses per year and we train more than 2000 customers every year.
Responsibilities
Commercially and clinically demonstrate the full range of products/services to prospects, to drive the sale of the product
Provide after-sales installation, training and/or customer service activities to support the business objectives of the geographical area during the life cycle of the product
Establish the credibility of the company with designated and new accounts as well as implement the clinical strategy.
Use your commercial and clinical experience to optimize and adjust products and position them on the market in coordination with the PCS Account Managers.
Responsible for the development and coordination of and delivery of the clinical application training
Responsible for training materials (course material, ppt, web solutions, etc.)
Provide clinical and technical support to account managers, input in tenders, demonstrations/test schedules and expertise during product presentations
Support at trade fairs and congresses with demonstrations, presentations and training
Work to increase customer satisfaction and patient safety through continuous training to enable our customers to use the systems fully and optimally
Assist the sales team with your knowledge of the market and products to assist in developing sales, marketing and customer service strategies
Responsible for reporting training results in writing and providing continuous feedback on customer satisfaction and needs
Qualifications/Requirements
Professional experience as a specialist nurse in anesthesia or intensive care
Experience of working in a global matrix organization
Good knowledge of Microsoft Office
Excellent ability to communicate in both speech and writing: Swedish and English
Interested in pedagogy and in/out learning processes
Be able to deliver at short notice and meet deadlines
Willing to travel a large part of your working hours, mainly in Sweden but sometimes to other parts of the Nordic region
EU work permit
Ability to travel in Sweden and valid driver’s license
Desirable features
You are a team player who can also work independently and run your own projects with increased customer satisfaction in focus
Be able to understand, present and explain advanced technology and concepts in a simple and positive way
Clinical experience in preop environment, ICU or cardiac care. Holter analysis and ECG interpretation is a plus
Professional in all receptions
High integrity
High professional competence
Flexible and willing to constantly strive for improvements
Advantage if you have in-depth knowledge and interest in monitoring parameters and ventilation
Advantage if you manage one or more of the other Nordic languages
Inclusion and Diversity
GE Healthcare is an Equal Opportunity Employer where inclusion matters. Employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, protected veteran status or other characteristics protected by law.
Our total rewards are designed to unlock your ambition by giving you the boost and flexibility you need to turn your ideas into world-changing realities. Our salary and benefits are everything you’d expect from an organization with global strength and scale, and you’ll be surrounded by career opportunities in a culture that fosters care, collaboration and support.
#LI-AG2
Additional Information
Relocation Assistance Provided: No

Title: Tech Lead for a Connected Features team within Autonomous...
Description:
For Zenseact it is a given that software deployed to cloud is a key part of our product. To solve the problem of true autonomy we need to leverage the power of not only individual vehicles, but entire fleets. We are challenging traditional ways of working with software within automotive to create a modern and leading eco-system of partners, data and end-user services around automated mobility.
Insights from the team
Our team is called Mimer, referring to a god in Norse mythology, renowned for his knowledge and wisdom ;). We are now growing the team and looking for a colleague who take pride in the art of developing great code for globally distributed and connected systems.
Currently we are four developers, with passion for areas such as security, optimization, Kubernetes and clean code. We work in an agile framework, with a product owner who demonstrates confidence in our ability to do the job, and with hands-on experience to chip in to our discussions. We work as a cross-functional team, where we collaborate tightly to have a common view on our strategy and the recommendations we provide. Far from being ivory towers, we work closely with the feature teams to provide guidance on a need basis, ensuring coherence where essential and hands on development of shared components.

Your Role
As a Tech Lead within the cloud and maps product-domain you will be a key person working with innovative connected features related to self-driving and advanced driver support. The role involves:
Leading and supporting teams in software and technical architecture work, specifically around cloud adoption
Create designs supporting both functional needs as well as taking care of performance, resilience, reuse, maintainability, scalability and security
Hands-on development of key functional components as well as tooling, patterns and guidelines
Drive process and tooling for CI/CD, verification and requirements
Your Profile
As a successful Tech Lead for Cloud and Maps at Zenseact you have a strong background in the full lifecycle of designing, developing, testing, deploying, operating and maintaining cloud based software solutions and managing individual project priorities, deadlines and deliverables. Furthermore, you have:
Experience building and operating large-scale systems in public cloud, specifically Microsoft Azure
Strong experience with one or more of Java, C++, python
Good communication and leadership skills
A self-starter with the ability to work effectively in teams and individually
Experience with any of this will give you an extra edge:
Cloud infrastructure automation, specifically Terraform
IoT or connected vehicle solutions
Stream analytics and processing technologies
Big data analytics
Mapping and GIS
IT Security
Operating global distributed system, especially including China
How do we work?
Flexible-remote way of working: Zenseact has a flexible and modern approach, thus is happy to offer to its employees the possibility for a combination of work at the office and from home. This doesn't include fully remote work from outside Sweden/China.
More about Zenseact

Zenseact’s purpose is to make safe and intelligent mobility real, for everyone, everywhere. We develop the complete software stack for ADAS and AD, from sensing to actuation. Our focus is to build a single cutting-edge software platform in order to serve various levels of autonomy and offer unequaled scalability at the same time. We operate out of Gothenburg, Sweden and Shanghai, China. Zenseact’s first self-driving deployment will be launched on the next-generation vehicle platform from Volvo Cars.

Self-driving cars, when real, is estimated to reduce fatal car accidents with more than 85%, saving more than 50,000 persons from dying in car accidents caused by human errors each year. We feel that is a goal worth pursuing.

But technology, software, tools and datasets would not mean much without the best people behind the wheel to drive them. At Zenseact, some five hundred of the best engineering minds globally, stationed across two continents, are collaborating with the same passion: to bring autonomous driving to the streets for real and create a safer journey for everyone. This is part of our culture and how we work, develop and grow together.
Zenseact works proactively to create a culture of diversity and inclusion, where individual differences are appreciated and respected. To drive innovation we see diversity as an asset, which means we value and respect differences in gender, race, ethnicity, religion or other belief, disability, sexual orientation or age etc.

Interviews are held on a continuous basis, so we highly recommend that you submit your application at your earliest convenience.

#LI-RR1

Title: Business & Process Development Leader, Customer Fulfilment
Description:
Who you are

We at Ingka are looking to transform how we are set up as an omnichannel retailer, to provide excellent first and last-mile service to our customers, securing both people, planet, and business interests. With the last mile, we mean deliveries to our customer’s homes. The first mile happens when we pick up goods, as the first step in the journey for returning, recycling, and reusing. As part of our IKEA Retail Direction, one of our jobs is to create affordable services to make IKEA convenient (Job 4). We continue to grow in our online sales and services and need to transform the last and first mile to secure our future as an omnichannel retailer.

You are motivated by improving the IKEA business and customer needs and influencing the improvement of the business with a focus on customer satisfaction by leading through co-creation with colleagues and other IKEA units. You are highly interested in the mix of strategic thinking and driving solution development. Independent and interdependent work energizes you, and you enjoy working across functions in an agile way to drive change.

Skills that would benefit you in this role:

Experience leading within the last mile & service fulfillment operations and/or sourcing to provide excellence in operations resulting in a seamless shopping experience.
Excellent knowledge of supply chain processes, precisely last mile & service operations, leading to excellent customer fulfillment.
Excellent knowledge of relevant digital solution landscapes associated with customer fulfillment, predominantly last mile, and services.
Good in change management and leading in the unknown - a forward-leaning approach and being open to thinking outside the box and challenging how we do things today.
Good at building relationships across the organisation.
Broad knowledge of identifying and involving relevant stakeholders in a project, process, or question to make things happen in a matrix organisation.

What you'll be doing day to day

We seek multiple Business and Process Development Leaders to join our Last & First-mile project team. The project will focus on creating new ways of working, tools, procedures, operating methods, and solutions supported and enabled by a modern and efficient digital landscape.

You will enable IKEA to transform by leading, coordinating, and supporting transformation activities. This will include the following:

Identifying, specifying, and building improved and new business processes in line with digital solutions and functionalities in close collaboration with Digital and Operations.
Proactively identifying and clustering business development needs, process improvements, and data analytics needs based on the everyday need of co-workers.
Leading, managing, and supporting business development and epics/features (hands-on short, mid, and long-term).
Provide in-depth knowledge of the development within the area of last mile & service fulfillment operations.
Responsible for process documentation (process maps, customer journey's working documentation, measurement specifications, learning material, epic descriptions, and SOPs).
Being an integral part of the line organisation to secure competence sharing, decision-making grounded in reality, and closeness to the IKEA retail countries.

The location for this role is Malmö or Amsterdam. This role requires some travel (depending on the prioritized activities) and is a temporary (3-year assignment).

Together as a team

Customer Fulfilment (CFF) is a core function within Retail Operations and a fundamental part of making IKEA Omnichannel retailing a reality. This we do by developing and operating replenishment and fulfillment end-to-end with a process-oriented organization, with radical collaboration with our colleagues within Commercial/Market Support, Digital, and Expansion.

We lead with a clear focus on people development and sustainable and cost-effective operations. In everything we do – we have a customer obsession with the aim of achieving 100% Happy Customers.

Questions and support? Let's connect!

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please feel free to contact the Recruiter, Talita Moraes Olsen, at talita.moraes.olsen@ingka.ikea.com. If you have any questions about the role, please get in touch with Alastair Morgan at alastair.morgan@ingka.ikea.com or Sebastian Krysén at sebastian.krysen1@ingka.ikea.com.

Studies show that members of underrepresented communities don’t apply for jobs unless they’re 100% “qualified”. If this is part of the reason you hesitate to apply, we would like you to reconsider and give it a chance. Maybe your profile fits our needs much better than you think. We look forward to receiving your application.

From: “Why Women Don’t Apply for Jobs Unless They’re 100% Qualified” by Tara Sophia Mohr, August 2014”

We look forward to receiving your application in English as soon as possible but no later than the 10th of February 2022.

PLEASE NOTE
Please respect that due to GDPR we cannot review any applications coming to us in other ways than through our recruitment program.

Title: Business Controller to Kollmorgen
Description:
We're looking for you, a Business Controller for one-year temporary position that wants to be a part of a global high-tech product company!

About the position
One of our colleagues will be on parental leave and therefore we are now looking for a Business Controller to help us take the next step in in the journey of Digitalizing Finance. We see great opportunities in the areas of rationalization, standardization, and visual management. In addition to that, you will also support the Product Management department with the pricing work.
Would you like to drive improvement by structuring data and reporting, and develop a state-of-the-art Visual Management? Are you structured, collaborative and have a good knowledge in Excel and at least basic understanding in Power BI? Do you want be part of a great team with high engagement, strong competence, and a great sense of humor? Then you should apply!
Key Responsibilities:
Your main tasks will be to structure data and develop reporting, to rationalize the closing process and weekly deliveries. You will build up standard work and standard processes related to Closing, Forecast, and Pricing and prepare visuals to the management team.
Your main focus will be development of reporting, but also be part of pricing work, closing activities and ad hoc tasks.
We are looking for you
... who enjoys being a part of a team that is working close together. As a person, you are analytical and with problem solving skills which makes you see the details as well as the bigger picture to not get stuck if something goes wrong. Furthermore, you plan your work to be able to easily deliver on time to meet business deadlines. We think that you also have some patience when hitting obstacles, such as technical issues.

Since we are a smaller company, we are looking for a person that enjoys learning new things to be able to work and preform in different areas, both now and in the future. Finally, you are a person that asks for help when you need it – no one can know everything and the team highly value tight collaboration and support to each other.

Preferred Experience and Knowledge
Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Finance, or a related field
3-5 years’ experience in a Finance, Business Control or Data Analytics
Strong knowledge in Excel (handling large amount of data, but no need for VBA)
Basic but preferably good knowledge in Power BI.

About us
Kollmorgen is a global company which develops motion control and Automated Guided Vehicle (AGV) systems and works with customers in many different industries all over the world.
Kollmorgen Automation is a part of Kollmorgen Corporation and we have our Swedish headquarter in Mölndal. The target is to provide world leading technology for the rapidly growing market of AGVs and Mobile Robots. The about 100 employees are working with product development, professional services, sales, marketing and finance.

Some of the good things that we offer
Innovation Days every twelve weeks - a 24-hour event for the whole company to dig deeper, explore new areas and solve problems!
Gym at the office filled with machines for strength and fitness that is always open and free to use for all our employees
Free parking outside our office
Noise cancelling headphones and home office equipment (office chair, screens etc)
Career opportunities within the company – we have employees who have worked with us for many years in different roles and departments
Day of Caring – every year we take one day to clean the west coast beaches together ️
6 weeks’ vacation! ️️
Work time reduction – it gives you around 7 extra days off per year
Collective agreement, occupational pension, wellness allowance

A part from above, Kollmorgen is characterized by an entrepreneurial spirit where you get the opportunity to carry out your ideas with the help of the company's experts.
We focus on engagement and personal development as essential tools for our success. We give you the opportunity to work in an open environment where ideas and thoughts are lifted freely among colleagues.
Additional information
80-100% employment, depending on your preferences. Temporary position, February 2023-March 2024. Based in Mölndal, Sweden. We recruit based on our values and for us it is important that you continuously want do develop yourself together with us!
Selection takes place on an ongoing basis, so send your application as soon as possible. If you have any questions about the position, reach out to hiring manager Joakim Hangby +46 732571237. Welcome with your application!
Check out more open positions,
️ follow us on Facebook,
get to know us better through our Candidate Blog,
️ and see videos about our products at our Youtube channel!

Title: Information & Integration Architect - Gothenburg
Description:
Veritaz is a fast-growing IT-consultant firm. Our company is made up of insanely bright people from over 4 countries, and we are located in Sweden, UK, US and Pakistan. The voyage has been incredible this far, but it is only the beginning.
Assignment Description:
We are looking for an Information Architect who is experienced in design and governance of Cloud based solutions in a hybrid scenario with on premise solutions.
Do you value openness, transparency, and empowerment? Our squad is high performing cross-functional team who are set with a mission to provide win-win exchanges for our customer.
What you'll do:
● Enable effective data and analytics governance, develop information governance processes and structures, as well as sources and classifications – in close collaboration with the Information Security and Data & Analytics teams.
● Conduct Business Information Modelling, create and manage business information models in all forms - including conceptual models, database designs, message models and others.
● Enhance decision-making and provide the organization with a view of the information landscape for strategic planning etc.
● Act as an Architecture Evangelist, active in forums, working groups, functional and regional areas to ensure that communication and alignment is maintained.
● Improve business performance through enterprise information solutions and capabilities (Master Data Management, Metadata Management, Analytics, Content Management, Data Integration, and related Information Management or Information Infrastructure Components.
Who you are:
● Have a relevant background with 10 years or more of experience in Information Architecture, Integration Architecture and Solution Design.
● Have an End-to-End process mindset, bridging between solution areas and applications to integration with standard and best practices as guiding principles.
● Good Knowledge of ERP Landscape, Process Architecture, and the ERP application portfolio.
● Excellent communication, teamwork skills, inter-personal and Organizational skills.
● Ability to translate business requirements into integration architecture requirements, roadmap, and deliverables.
Job Type: Full-time
Ability to commute/relocate:
Stockholm: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Preferred)
Application Question(s):
What is your salary expectations?
When will you be available to join?
Do you need a sponsor with a Swedish working permit?
What is your level of proficient in Swedish?
Work authorization:
Sweden (Preferred)

Title: Patient Safety IT Project Manager
Description:
Patient Safety IT Project Manager
Do you have expertise in, and passion for, Patient Safety? Would you like to apply your expertise to impact a company that follows the science and turns ideas into life changing medicines? If so, AstraZeneca might be the one for you!
ABOUT ASTRAZENECA
AstraZeneca is a global, innovation-driven BioPharmaceutical business that focuses on the discovery, development and commercialisation of prescription medicines for some of the world’s most serious disease. But we’re more than one of the world’s leading pharmaceutical companies.
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
ABOUT OUR IT TEAM
Here our work has a direct impact on patients – transforming our ability to develop life-changing medicines. We empower the business to perform at its peak and lead a new way of working, combining pioneering science with leading digital technology platforms and data. All with a passion to impact lives through data, analytics, AI, machine learning and more. Join us at a crucial stage of our journey in becoming a digital and data-led enterprise. Make the impossible possible by building partnerships and ecosystems, creating new ways of working
and driving scale and speed to deliver exponential growth. Focused and committed, and backed with the investment to succeed, we’re driving cross-company change to disrupt the entire industry. Ours is a place to innovate, take ownership and run with it. You’re trusted to explore and to find new solutions, experimenting with groundbreaking technology and grappling with challenges in a modern technology environment that might never have been tackled before. It’s a dynamic and challenging environment to work in – but that’s why we like it. There are countless opportunities to learn and grow, whether that’s exploring new technologies in hackathons, or transforming the roles and work of colleagues, forever. Shape your own path, with support all the way. Diverse minds that work cross-functionally and inclusively together. Be part of a team that has the backing to innovate, disrupt an industry and change lives.
ABOUT THE ROLE?
You will work with business units in R&D, focusing on Patient Safety. You will
be an authority and advocate for the Patient Safety organization, working collaboratively as part of a customer-facing R&D IT team. In this role,
you will work closely with other Project Managers and Business Analysts in Patient Safety, Regulatory, Quality & Clinical Development capability as well as broader R&D IT, and be expected to develop and leverage relationships with strategic external partners and a global IT matrix spanning 3,000+ people across the US, UK, Sweden, China, Japan, Poland, and India. Patient Safety Project Managers are expected to develop domain and technical expertise across Patient Safety.

The Project Manager will manage a major project (valued in excess of $2M) within a function or geography or a major workstream within Patient Safety programme. The role will report to the Patient Safety Senior Program Manager. The role will lead a project team from initiation to close, to deliver effective solutions that meet approved customer and business needs. Project / Programme Managers are accountable for determining and delivering solutions to approved budget and schedule commitments whilst meeting required quality and compliance standards. Focus areas include Risk Management and delivery of business benefit. This role is also required to follow established project management standards and contribute to continued development of the project management capability.
TYPICAL ACCOUNTABILITIES
Agree and deliver plans for projects / programmes (or contribution in part to a larger project), including activities, resources, costs, roles, responsibilities and quality as defined in the IT Project Management Methodology (ADF).
Manage project / programme budgets, forecasts, tasks, schedules, risks, change management, and status to support effective decisions and project reporting to partners and review boards. Coordinate status and delivery of project workstreams. Identify / manage dependencies between projects (intra-program and across portfolio).
Assure / develop service transition plans to ensure project delivered solutions are sustainable within a BAU operations environment, including controlled hand-over into operational support.
Manage relationships with key business partners to ensure the effective capturing of business requirements and commitment to project/program objectives. Responsible for steering / collaborator meetings, communication of status, issues, risks.
Ensure effective risks & issues management processes are in place and effectively used. Resolve problems and raise as appropriate.
Build a cohesive project team and provide the leadership necessary to improve the team’s success. Provide individual coaching and development of team members as needed.
Manage changes to project/programme scope, ensuring that all impacts and changes are approved and appropriately communicated to partners and review boards.
Develop service transition plans including controlled hand-over into support and maintenance.
Ensure the project team adheres to all standards including ADF, quality, and compliance, as well as processes, defined technical capabilities, and standard methodologies. Establish program governance and lead Decision Point reviews; member Steering Committee.
Ensure expected benefits realization is consistent with project deliverables and clearly understood by collaborators and project team.
Support continued development of a world-class centre of excellence for project management capabilities and ensure that standard process is adopted and reinforced.
Typical project cost in the range of $100k - $1m, with a project team of up to 12 people.
Effectively collaboratively with:
Supplier Management function to manage delivery of small to medium-sized supplier contracts Internal and External Suppliers to ensure delivery of agreed products and services while ensuring adherence to AZ project delivery standards Key business customers to ensure the effective capturing of business requirements and commitment to project/programme objectives
ESSENTIAL SKILLS & EXPERIENCE REQUIRED?
Technical or Business Degree or relevant proven experience
Proven skills and experience managing and controlling project budgets
Experience leading and developing project teams with a diverse blend of skills and capabilities
Evidence of shaping innovative solutions that have a major impact within the business area and organisation
Proven relevant experience as an Associate PM or equivalent role.
Strong Project and Programme Management Skills
Proven problem solving capabilities.
A capable knowledge of Financial Management and Benefits Delivery practices.
Broad understanding of IT systems and technology implemented within a business context.
Strong communication, relationship and consulting skills
Knowledge and experience with internal and external suppliers and solutions
Excellent intuition for business with sensitivity to environment
Experience with project management and delivery methodologies and standards
WHY JOIN US?
We’re a network of entrepreneurial self-starters who contribute to something far bigger. There’s a diversity of expertise in our Technology group that’s unique to AstraZeneca – it allows us to dive deep into
exploring new groundbreaking technology. We enable AstraZeneca to perform at its peak by delivering world-class technology and data solutions. Our work unlocks the potential of science. We optimise and evolutionise AstraZeneca by maximising efficiencies and finding new ways to drive productivity. From automation to data simplification. We’re not afraid to take ownership and run with it. Empowered with unrivalled freedom. A place to be open and transparent – we speak up, think creatively and share ideas. Our diverse contributions help us to make better decisions. But we have a constant drive to innovate,
and an appreciation for high standards. It takes challenging the status quo to contribute in our ever-evolving environment. We love it here because put simply, we make a meaningful impact.
Technology at AstraZeneca is a home for purposeful disruptors!
SO, WHAT’S NEXT?
Are you already imagining yourself joining our team? Good, because we’d love to hear from you! Click the link to apply and we’ll be in touch as soon as we can.
WHERE CAN I FIND OUT MORE?

Title: Marketing - Project Manager - Trainee
Description:
Landell Games AB was established in 2021 and performs consulting work in IT such as infrastructure, due diligence, and the manufacture of software such as video games and innovative technology.
We are looking for a Project Manager that would help our Head of Marketing with their day-to-day tasks and would join us for 6 months part-time (minimum 20h/week) or full-time with the opportunity to extend it further, and since we are in discussions with big names in the video game industry, we plan to start our recruitment process shortly.
It is important to note that the internship period is unpaid.
Our Marketing Team is growing fast and we are in need of a person who would take care of some tasks done by our Head of Marketing on a day-to-day basis.
Your assignments would consist of helping the other Leads with their issues and making sure that everything runs smoothly. You would also have the opportunity to be a part of planning and executing all project ideas, monitoring the projects and setting deadlines for different teams within the Marketing Team.
The most important attribute you need is a strong drive to learn and see things through, and if you are ready to put in sweat and tears, we are ready to provide you with a unique skill set that will help us reach our goals and help you build an impressive portfolio for your future endeavors in the gaming industry.
Examples of assignments:
- Making sure that the content calendar is on time and without errors
- Overseeing and understanding the expansion of our community on existing and new social networks
- Briefing the new members and making sure that they reach their optimal work levels
- Researching new ways and funnels that will allow us to reach out target audience
- Effectively communicating instructions and finding solutions to the problems encountered by other Leads and teams
- Motivating the teams, understanding their needs and nurturing the positive work environment
Who we are:
We pride ourselves on being hardworking, determined and passionate. Positive mindset and hunger for knowledge are in our blood and we are always happy to help each other out and welcome new members to the project. The team itself works together remotely and has many years of combined experience in the growing gaming industry and is growing by the day, with more than 40 gaming enthusiasts currently working on the project.
We are very open to sharing our knowledge and we encourage every member to be inquisitive about the methods and progress of their own team, as well as about the other departments. Voicing one's opinion is extremely important in our mission of game development and self betterment, so we see it as a quality of motivated individuals and welcome it on every occasion.
We offer you to:
- Shape your own way of working and choose your working hours with us
- Get the opportunity to learn from practical experience in Marketing, namely Data Analytics and Influncer Management
- Work on an ambitious project that you can use in your portfolio
- Learn about developing a game as a whole
- Make invaluable connections
- Have fun and hopefully make lifelong friendships
Who you are:
- First and foremost, a passionate gamer who sincerely wants an opportunity to work in the gaming industry
- An independent individual not afraid to ask questions, solve problems and address issues
- A creative, inquisitive and detail oriented person who is willing to make their own decisions and are genuinely excited to learn and develop their knowledge within marketing in gaming industry
Requirements:
- Fluency in English
- Basic understanding of Excel and/or Google sheets
- Willingness and ability to dedicate at least 20 hours a week to the project for the period of at least 6 months
Additional (not required) skills:
- Experience with influencer management
- Previous experience as a team lead
- Experience with promoting gaming content on social media
- Experience with Kickstarter Campaigns
- Basic understanding of Social Media insights and analytics
Read more about the game project at: https://DawnofEmpires.com
Attach your Resume/CV together with a short description of why you would be the best fit for us.
We are looking forward to getting to know you better!
Jobbtyp: Heltid, Deltid, Vikariat, Praktik, Trainee
Avtalslängd: 5 månader
Arbetstider:
Måndag till fredag
Flexible Language Requirement:
Svenskkunskap krävs inte

Title: Calvia söker C# .NET-utvecklare
Description:
Calvia befinner sig i en expansiv fas och söker nu fler C# / .NET-utvecklare och som gillar att ligga på framkant när det gäller nya tekniker och metoder, t ex Azure DevOps, Cloud, CI/CD, TDD, Microservices, SQL databaser, Elastic search, Angular/React och tillhörande teknologier och metoder.

Vi tror på samarbete, kontinuerlig kompetensutveckling, agil utveckling av både företaget och i programutveckling. Genom att samarbeta och stötta varandra blir allt roligare, kunderna nöjdare och kakan större. Vår inriktning är verksamhetsnära IT i Göteborgsområdet med fokus på .NET-utveckling och Data Analytics.

Vill du dessutom vara med och påverka din och företagets utveckling erbjuder vi en mycket fördelaktig partner-modell för delägande och vinstdelning och där varje konsult får ett stort inflytande på sin och företagets prioriteringar för att skapa bästa tänkbara utveckling, glädje, trivsel och framgång.

Vi brinner för:
Kontinuerlig kompetensutveckling
Agilt arbetssätt baserat på delaktighet, samarbete och förtroende
Goda kundrelationer präglat av öppenhet, samarbete, långsiktighet och ärlighet.
En mix av ålder, erfarenhet och kön ger fler perspektiv
Utmaningar, framgångar och vinster delas solidariskt
Balans i livet, goda relationer och stor flexibilitet
Låter detta intressant så vill vi gärna träffa dig och höra vilka områden du brinner för, vilken typ av uppdrag du är intresserad av samt vilka tankar du har kring din utveckling och vad som är viktigt för att du skall trivas.

Hör av dig så berättar vi mer.

Vi sitter på AWL (A Working Lab) inne på Chalmers-området, Johanneberg.

Flytande svenska i tal och skrift är ett krav.
Stämmer detta in på dig? Då vill vi träffa dig!

Kristian Persson
