Title: SOFTWARE ENGINEER TILL SKÖVDE
Description:
Skövde
Till teamet inom software i Skövde söker vi personer med 1-2 års erfarenhet inom områdena systemutveckling, data analytics och IoT. I rollen som Employeneur får du både utveckla dina tekniska kunskaper och driva din egen utveckling och affär. Du blir del av en innovativ och entreprenöriell organisation där fokuset ligger på ständig utveckling och möjligheten att vara fullt ansvarig för din egen karriär.

| VEM ÄR DET VI SÖKER?
Vi lägger stor vikt vid ditt personliga engagemang och din vilja att driva din utveckling framåt. För att lyckas med det ges du chansen att själv påverka vilken typ av projekt du tar dig an samt vilken kompetensutveckling du vill investera i. Du styr din karriär helt enkelt.
Som Employeneur i teamet inom Software kommer du att arbeta med utveckling av mjukvara tillsammans med våra kunder runt om i Skaraborg. Arbetsuppgifterna är många och innefattar bland annat Back End/Front End utveckling inom olika programmeringsspråk, utveckling av industri 4.0 med IoT, och testautomation. Att jobba tillsammans med andra i en dynamisk miljö med tvärvetenskapliga discipliner, gör att du vässar dina tekniska färdigheter och även din sociala förmåga när du samarbetar med dina kollegor.
Vi är nyfikna på dig som är utbildad högskole- eller civilingenjör och ser gärna att du jobbat något år i rollen som software engineer. Då man arbetar med ständiga förbättringar är detta något som du drivs av och tycker är intressant. Vi förutsätter att du kan både engelska och svenska flytande.
Meriterande om du har tidigare erfarenhet av:
C# och .Net
Testautomation
JavaScript
CSS
C++
Python
Java
Microsoft Azure
Agila utvecklingsprocesser
| VAD KAN TMC ERBJUDA DIG?
Genom Employeneurship-modellen är TMC unika. Det är affärsmodellen för 2000-talets ingenjörer och den bygger på fem pelare:

A LONG TERM WORKING RELATIONSHIP
På TMC kombinerar du säkerheten av en trygg anställning med de möjligheter som entreprenörskap erbjuder. Detta eliminerar osäkerheten man kan uppleva som konsult eller entreprenör och du får mer tid och energi till att fokusera på ditt arbete och dina långsiktiga ambitioner och mål.

INDIVIDUAL PROFIT SHARING
Employeneurship-modellen erbjuder en marknadsmässig grundlön samtidigt som dina entreprenöriella förmågor premieras och du tar del av vinsten. Du som Employeneur har möjlighet att själv påverka säljprocessen utifrån din kompetens och vi är transparenta när det kommer till både din omsättning och dina kostnader. Känn ditt marknadsvärde och dela vinsten som ditt arbete genererar!

BUSINESS CELLS
Som Employeneur tillhör du en Business Cell baserat på ditt tekniska kompetensområde. Dessa specialistområden utgår från teknologiska nischkompetenser och skapar nätverk mellan dig och andra Employeneurer med liknande bakgrund. Du som Employeneur blir del av ett starkt och relevant internationellt nätverk som möjliggör ett delat engagemang i kombination med kunskaps- och erfarenhetsutbyte.

YOUNIVERSITY
TMC värderar dig som Employeneur högt och har utvecklat ett program för att garantera din personliga och professionella utveckling, din YOUrney. YOUniversity är ett unikt program för din utveckling och är tänkt att stödja dig genom din karriär. Genom personlig 1-1 coaching får du möjlighet att utvecklas, både som individ och i ditt entreprenörskap. Att ge dig möjlighet till både personlig och professionell utveckling ser vi som bästa möjliga investering!

THE ENTREPENEURIAL LAB
The Entrepreneurial Lab erbjuder utrymme för Employeneurer inom TMC att samarbeta över gränser. Vi vill att du ska förverkliga dina drömmar och utveckla ditt entreprenörskap. The Entrepreneurial Lab drivs av en självgående proaktiv attityd hos dig som Employeneur som skapar värde för dig själv men självklart också för våra kunder. Se The Entrepreneurial Lab som en lekplats för nya idéer, produkter som tjänster.

Eftersom TMC är ett internationellt företag kan vi erbjuda projekt på olika platser i olika länder där vi och våra kunder finns. För närvarande finns vi representerade i Sverige, Nederländerna, Belgien, Frankrike, Spanien, Portugal, Italien, U.A.E., USA och Kanada. Du får världen som arbetsplats!

| VARFÖR EMPLOYENEURSHIP?
Uttrycket Employeneurship kanske låter obekant, det beror på att vi uppfann det. Inte bara som ett ord utan som ett sätt att arbeta, eller till och med ett paradigm. Att vara Employeneur är mycket mer än att bara arbeta som teknisk konsult. Denna unika roll ger dig möjlighet att tänka och agera som en entreprenör i kombination med den trygghet en anställning ger. Viktigast av allt - du får en garanti för ständig utveckling och möjligheten att vara fullt ansvarig för din egen karriär.

Ta chansen att vara del av vår växande verksamhet. Ansök så pratar vi mer om din plan!
Feel Free to Contact
Olof Lennartsson
Business Manager, Sweden
Tel: +46 70 971 08 64

Title: Lead, Computer Vision
Description:
With 950 employees, over $250M in sales, 1,500+ clients, and rapid year-over-year growth, Recorded Future is the world's most advanced, and largest, intelligence company!
Lead, Computer Vision
Location: Goteborg, London, Boston or remote
We are looking for an outstanding software engineer and engineering lead with a passion in computer vision, software engineering, and data analytics to join Recorded Future's Analytics Team within the R&D organization. You will join a group of talented engineers and data scientists who share a common interest in solving challenging analytical problems in large distributed systems with big data. The team's responsibilities include core parts of the analytics pipeline, such as data collection, analytics pipeline, framework, image processing, etc. We strive to turn our data into actionable intelligence and have fun.
You would get the chance to develop great analytics and software in a fast-moving environment close to our global clients and their needs. Together, we'll improve our product to meet increasing demands while focusing on speed, scalability, and quality. You will also investigate and experiment with new technology and explore the most suitable solutions for solving real-world problems internally and with 3rd party solutions. You would join a dynamic team eager to take on new challenges and passionate about their work.
What you will be doing:
You will be instrumental in building and implementing our new pipeline for analyzing and processing images, videos, and speech-to-text that address clients' use cases
Own and lead strategy and roadmap of the Image Analytics Product Team by creating continuity over 12 rolling months and 3 Horizons outline in close collaboration with a PO, PM, and Architect
Actively build prototypes and proof of concepts for selected investigations
Ensure that agreed investigations are naturally incorporated into the ongoing Product Team workload and an integral part of ongoing sprints
Be on a watch for the new technologies and services that will create value
Work with the Product Leadership to identify, translate, and formulate business needs into tractable Computer Vision problems
Implement robust, scalable, and efficient solutions using the best software engineering and computer vision techniques in a Product Team
Take ownership and be proactive; you are an expert
Support Product Owner in managing actual implementation and deliverables within Sprints. Participate in Sprints actively by taking on actual assignments and hands-on development, taking on the Sprint Master role and actual engineering tickets
On daily abscess, Continue to bring the team together and manage work efficiency by prioritizing, parallelizing workload and activities, ensuring work is executed within the sprint plan, and eliminating wasted activities
Participate in selected releases in the lead developer role, support others or yourself design the solution, and write/lead solution document/design or actual development
Actively take on initiatives supporting Analytics Team development
You will need the following:
MSc or preferably Ph.D. in Computer Science, Machine Learning, Computer Vision, or a related technical field
Expert-level experience in image analysis and computer vision applications
Implement and optimize analytics and machine learning algorithms using special-purpose computing architectures
Propose and implement creative, efficient solutions for image analysis and processing problems
Excellent knowledge of and experience with working with a variety of methods for analyzing image data, from classical to modern neural network-based methods
Excellent programming skills in Python and preferably other programming languages, especially Scala or Java
Ability to take the initiative and communicate/collaborate across teams both locally and globally
English is a must
Demonstrated track record of dealing well with ambiguity, prioritizing needs, and delivering results in a dynamic environment
Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to effectively advocate technical solutions to research scientists, engineering teams, and business audiences
Diversity has been essential to Recorded Future since day one, which is clearly visible in all teams in the company, yet there's always room for improvement. We welcome applications that will help us improve this even more.

#LI-Remote
Why should you join Recorded Future?
Recorded Future employees (or "Futurists"), represent over 40 nationalities and embody our core values of having high standards, practicing inclusion, and acting ethically. Our dedication to empowering clients with intelligence to disrupt adversaries has earned us a 4.7-star user rating from Gartner and 8 of the top 10 Fortune 100 companies as clients.
Want more info?
Blog & Podcast: Learn everything you want to know (and maybe some things you'd rather not know) about the world of cyber threat intelligence
Instagram & Twitter: What's happening at Recorded Future
The Record: The Record is a cybersecurity news publication that explores the untold stories in this rapidly changing field
Timeline: History of Recorded Future
Recognition: Check out our awards and announcements
We are committed to maintaining an environment that attracts and retains talent from a diverse range of experiences, backgrounds and lifestyles. By ensuring all feel included and respected for being unique and bringing their whole selves to work, Recorded Future is made a better place every day.

If you need any accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to our recruiting team at careers@recordedfuture.com

Recorded Future is an equal opportunity and affirmative action employer and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply. Recorded Future does not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, gender including pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, marital status, veteran status, disability or any other characteristic protected by law.

Recorded Future will not discharge, discipline or in any other manner discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment because such employee or applicant has inquired about, discussed, or disclosed the compensation of the employee or applicant or another employee or applicant.

Title: Client Director, Manufacturing - Sweden/Nordics
Description:
Client Director, Manufacturing – Sweden/Nordics
The Client Director role requires a proven ability to sell professional services including digital, engineering services and sourcing offerings to senior management including CIOs, CDOs’, CFOs, Global Business Services Leaders, CPOs, COOs and others, and the successful candidate will have a demonstrable track record of achievement.
Our Smart Manufacturing Vertical (SMV) supports the world's leading Automotive & Manufacturing organizations by helping them optimize their internal operations, modernize their legacy environments, and meet ever-increasing customer expectations whilst supporting digital business and IT transformations.

Position Overview
The role also demands the generation of SMV industry visibility by speaking at conferences, events, webcasts, writing articles, blogs, etc. and other sales generating opportunities as required. Whilst support will be available from the existing SMV team, it is expected that the successful candidate will be able to:
Identify sales opportunities with both existing and new clients, across the entire ISG service portfolio.
Work with SMV colleagues and our solution leads to develop appropriate solutions.
Lead and support sales pursuits.
Laser focused targeting of 15 manufacturing clients in the SMB DACH portfolio (3B€+) and develop those opportunities.
Close sales.
Expected approx. to deliver 40%-50% of capacity on sold projects and help building up new key accounts
Role & Responsibilities
Meets / exceeds annual sales, revenue and pipeline building performance quotas.
Actively calls on prospects to identify, qualify, manage and close opportunities in new and targeted existing accounts.
Creates and manages a robust pipeline of qualified new business opportunities sufficient to meet annual quotas.
Works closely with SMV leadership to translates strategic objectives into market-specific messaging and go-to-market efforts.
Market calling, prospect selection, activity tracking, and reporting.
Determines optimal prospect contact strategies and develop approaches to achieve prospect and account goals.
Provides market expertise and direction to event marketing team to maximize lead generation and professionally manage follow-up.
Increases SMVs leadership visibility through speaking engagements, and writing articles etc.
Applies expertise to sales process management, contact administration and organizational effectiveness.
Participates in service provider dialogues for lead generation.
Regularly updates sales pipeline for reporting purposes.
Assumes the role of business owner for opportunity management on ISG’s proprietary tools.
Essential Skillset
Industrial & automotive industry experience is essential.
Experience carrying and meeting an annual sales and revenue quota for personal production.
10+ years of industry experience working in a strategic/targeted account sales environment managing “global” clients and selling large consulting /professional services engagements.
Extensive existing network of potential clients to be leveraged by ISG in this new role.
High energy and level of professionalism in working the market and building and cultivating relationships.
Effective team-seller, who can collaborate and orchestrate the roles of ISG SMEs and leadership in a sales cycle.
Identifies with and can communicate the unique ISG value proposition.
Able to align Client & ISG Strategic objectives as well as ISG integrated offerings to help achieve Client’s business goals.
Deep understanding of factors impacting the SMV industry and how ISG can help address the Client’s business challenges.
Strong listening and consultative problem-solving skills with an ability to visualize and shape large integrated offerings from ISG.
Best in class executive “C” level sales & communications skills. Able to converse in business value terminology and appreciates the nuances between the BFSI sub-domains (retail banking, capital markets, asset/wealth management etc.).
Creative and strategic thinking with an ability to create and execute on effective account plans.
Effective leadership skills with demonstrable sharing of best practices.
Sincere integrity and ethics which builds trustworthy relationships internally and externally with an unspoken commitment to follow-up and follow through.
Proven communications skills for both writing, speaking and presentation.
Conveys a professional, polished image and the highest of professional ethics while maintaining a strong company attitude.
Key traits and characteristics include high energy, empathic, transparent, consultative, thick skinned, hungry to succeed, strong commercial skills, strong domain knowledge and a strong personal contact network.
Person Specification
Exceptional communicator in terms of verbal and written presentation skills. Able to effectively articulate a unique value proposition that resonates with client needs.
Excellent listening skills.
Strong SMV network and understanding of workings within SMV.
Experience as a team player in coordinating and implementing pursuit processes, including development of targeted and compelling proposals.
Conveys a professional image and maintains a strong company attitude.
Demonstrated experience of sound business judgment and superior business acumen.
Strong presence and influential traits to convince C level of value add.
Highly self-motivated, needing minimal support, training and guidance from management; however, keeps them appropriately informed.
Excellent time management, organizational and project management skills to maximize on time output and results.
Active participant in industry social networking, trade shows and corporate events.
Education
Bachelor of Arts or Science degree in a technical or scientific field or equivalent.
MBA or another advanced degree (s) desirable.
ISG (Information Services Group) (Nasdaq: III) is a leading global technology research and advisory firm. A trusted business partner to more than 700 clients, including more than 75 of the world’s top 100 enterprises, ISG is committed to helping corporations, public sector organizations, and service and technology providers achieve operational excellence and faster growth. The firm specializes in digital transformation services, including automation, cloud and data analytics; sourcing advisory; managed governance and risk services; network carrier services; strategy and operations design; change management; market intelligence and technology research and analysis. Founded in 2006, and based in Stamford, Conn., ISG employs more than 1,300 digital-ready professionals operating in more than 20 countries—a global team known for its innovative thinking, market influence, deep industry and technology expertise, and world-class research and analytical capabilities based on the industry’s most comprehensive marketplace data.
At ISG, we don’t just accept difference — we celebrate it, we support it, and we thrive on it for the benefit of our employees, our clients, and our communities. We are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. ISG is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and we are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. The more diverse and inclusive we are, the better our work will be.
The duties and responsibilities described in this job description may not be a comprehensive list. Additional tasks may be assigned to the employee from time to time and/or the scope of the job may change as necessitated by business demands.

Title: Data Center Production Operations Engineer
Description:
Meta is seeking a forward-thinking experienced Engineer to join the Production Operations Engineering team within Infra Data Centers. Our data centers, and the hundreds of thousands of servers installed in them, are the foundation upon which our rapidly scaling infrastructure efficiently operates and upon which our innovative services are delivered. Meta is at the leading edge of the global data center industry both in terms of how data centers are designed and operated. This person should enjoy working in a fast paced, technical environment where adaptability and flexibility will be key to their success. We seek an IT professional with advanced, hands-on technical skills in server hardware and Linux (ideally in a Data Center environment). Having extensive knowledge of server administration and performing on complex projects in a large-scale distributed data center environment is a core competency of this individual. The candidate should also have deep knowledge and experience in at least one of the following core areas: Hardware, OS repair, Tooling and Automation and Project Management.


Data Center Production Operations Engineer Responsibilities:
Perform deep dives and analysis of complex technical issues within the data center, ranging from automated tooling to hardware failures and network issues.
Work as a subject matter expert with cross functional teams on large scale data center projects and initiatives.
Provide cross data center support and identify potentially larger issues, displaying effective communication when something is identified.
Work with internal hardware teams and vendors to help drive complex technical issues to resolution, provide an ownership stake in ensuring high quality levels of hardware, and influence future design to ensure ease of serviceability.
Ability to solve issues at scale using scripting, automation and tooling
Use data analytics to drive maximum server fleet up-time and utilization rates by understanding hardware failure rates and SLAs to customers. Identify trends and systemic issues in the fleet and drive resolution.
Coach/Mentor team members to evaluate and identify better ways to resolve issues and define updates to tools and processes.
Provide mentorship and be the go-to technical resource for management.
Build cross functional relationships and have the ability to influence policies and procedures to improve global data center operations.
Participate in an on-call rotation.



Minimum Qualifications:
5+ years of technical IT experience within an infrastructure environment, in a role such as system administrator, dev/ops engineer, or SRE (Site Reliability Engineer)
Experience using Linux to support hardware systems in a complex IT environment.
Hands on experience and knowledge of hardware systems and components.
Time and project management experience
Knowledge of enterprise level networking and storage platforms.
Ability to triage, debug, troubleshoot complex systemic issues in a Linux server environment.
BS, BA or BEng in technical field or commensurate experience.
Experience managing multiple technical issues concurrently
Knowledge of the interdependencies of data center functions and technologies including electrical, cooling, structured cabling, security, network and server systems.
Solid oral and written communication skills. English as a working language.



Preferred Qualifications:
Experience in providing technical guidance to external vendors.
Experience in debugging, modifying and developing in commonly used scripting or programming languages including Bash, PHP, Python, SQL, or Perl.
Knowledge of out-of-band/lights-out server communication methods, such as IPMI and serial console.
Experience in a large-scale data center environment.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Pushing boundaries for a sustainable future
The world is dealing with an environmental crisis and energy crisis, and we, as Vargas Holding’s latest venture, are actively creating a sustainable future. We provide renewable energy solutions to everyday homes to help them cut their dependency on oil and gas, electrify their energy consumption, and to control their energy bill. To solve the climate and energy crisis, we are at the forefront of creating innovative solutions that accelerate the creation of smart and sustainable homes.

Heating alone represents some 15% of the EU's CO2 emissions and switching to a sustainable energy solution is by far the easiest way for a household to make a real impact. That's why we are dedicated to developing solutions that not only combat these crises and create sustainable homes but also empower homeowners to take control of their energy consumption and save money on their energy bills.
Our goal is to cut homeowners’ dependency on fossil fuels and help them transition to clean, renewable energy sources. We make it possible for everyone to combat the climate crisis. With a firm belief in the power of innovation and technology, we build solutions for today’s challenges, and for those of tomorrow – for current and our next generations. By transforming local energy consumption, we will create a global transformation.
We are passionate about making a positive impact on the world, and we believe that by creating smart and sustainable homes, we can do just that. We hope you will join us in this important work as we strive to make a difference in the fight against the climate crisis.

About the role
We are looking for a Data Engineer to join our brand-new Data Analytics and ML team. We are looking for somebody who can build our data pipelines from the ground up. You are responsible for making our data accessible and serving it in an easily consumed format. Your work will be key to optimizing the reliability and performance of our organization and the different teams. You will build and maintain our data landscape, drive change in our development processes, engineer solutions to enhance features, and be a part of our data architecture to propel solutions to further levels.
Your other responsibilities include:
Enable data- and AI-driven software, insights and informed decisions through serving data assets in an interoperable, agile and modern fashion
Contribute to shaping our common, purpose-built data landscape, from early phases to global scale
Develop end-to-end pipelines to ingest, transform and serve data assets
Collaborate with software product development teams to enable them autonomy in serving and consuming data in the landscape
Introduce practices and tools to improve data reliability and performance
Provide crucial data to adjust future business strategies
Provide enriched data and analytics capabilities to enable discussions and motivate decisions


Who are you

From a technical perspective we would like you to have experience with:
Data engineering and building pipelines from the ground up
Understanding and analysing Big Data Architecture
Creating ELT/ETL pipelines ingesting and transforming data
Creating data analysis tools and validation methods
Building, testing, and maintaining database and pipeline architectures
Experience with Java, SQL, Scala, Spark, and Python
Experience with CICD and deployment pipeline principles
Experience with data/analytics/ML in any major cloud platform
As a person we would like you to be:
Adaptable and hands-on solution while taking into account/having an interest for the holistic perspective
A quick learner with a willingness to share knowledge
A strong communicator and teamplayer

What we offer
Besides a competitive salary and secondary benefits, we offer the opportunity to build a global company and product with true environmental impact. Our team is led by top engineers from IKEA, H&M, Svea Solar, Volvo, Scania, Viaplay, and Kry, bringing a wealth of experience and expertise to the table.
As a member of our team, you'll have the chance to be a part of a fast-moving growth journey with far-reaching learning and development opportunities. You'll have the chance to work with some of the most talented and innovative professionals in the industry, dedicated to making a positive impact on the world through our products and services. You'll be able to contribute to the development of cutting-edge technology that has the potential to make a significant positive impact on the world.
In addition to the opportunity to contribute to a meaningful and impactful company, you'll also have access to ongoing learning and development opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally. We believe that our team is our greatest asset, and we are committed to fostering a supportive and inclusive culture that empowers our employees to reach their full potential.
Whether you're an experienced professional or just starting out in your career, we believe that everyone has the potential to make a meaningful contribution to our mission. So, if you're passionate about building a better future and want to be a part of something special, we'd love to have you join us. So, come and join our team and be a part of building a truly global company with a product that makes a real difference in the world.
Don't hesitate and send us your application today! If you have any questions regarding applications or else, contact me at line.thomson@vargasholding.se

Title: Knowledge graph consultant - Stockholm
Description:
Join our international community within knowledge graph technology, where you get to exchange experiences and knowledge with other knowledge graph experts within Capgemini.
We are Scandinavia's leading data, analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards a data-driven decisions.
What You’ll Do
As a Knowledge graph consultant, you will help our clients making better data-driven decisions by modeling and building robust data flows, creating an efficient data transporter, and building data architecture for Machine Learning solutions and BI solutions. You will also work with the development of computer science solutions stars on graph technology.
Our clients exploit all capabilities of the W3C Semantic Stack (RDF, RDFS, SPARQL, OWL, SHACL), graph databases and ontology modelling tools. While others focus more on tech stack like Neo4j, Cypher or Labeled Property Graph implementations.
We like to see that you have experience with some or several of above-mentioned technologies!
We also like to combine knowledge graphs with Natural Language Processing, meaning this might also be the perfect opportunity for someone with a background as linguist combined with a great interest in knowledge graphs.
You will be given the opportunity to work with a variation of clients located across Northern Europe. We work in a hybrid working model, meaning that, from time to time you might be asked to travel while on other occasions work remotely. To be successful in the role, we think that you thrive in an international environment, where you generously share your domain knowledge within Graph technology.
We hope that you enjoyed reading this job description and that this is exactly what you are looking for since you have a background within semantics, logic or linguistic.
We look forward to receiving your application!
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
You need to have:
Domain experience in knowledge graph technologies, you also enjoy solving complex modeling problems.
Knowledge about Linked Data Concepts
ETL processes with various graph databases.
Experience in Interaction with graph databases through standardized APIs and query languages
Information and Data Management
Curiosity and eagerness to learn new things
Programming skills (specific language is not required, but we use Python, Java or .Net)
Semantic technologies:
Utilize (W3C) Standards of the Semantic Stack
Knowledge regarding several datavases or excellent on at least one
Modelling knowledge with ontologies using various tools.
Skills for LPG
Knowledge regarding several databases or excellent on at least one.
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Architectural thinking
Data virtualization
Data mapping
Graph analysis
Graph visualization
Lifecycle Management of knowledge graphs in an enterprise environment
Skills for semantic technologies
Advanced reasoning and RDF validation
Skills for LPG
Machine Learning on Graphs

Title: Postdoc fellowships in Data-driven development and High-Performance Computing
Description:
Welcome to Linnaeus University! We meet the societal challenges of today and tomorrow in a spirit of openness, curiosity and creativity. By creating arenas for exchange of knowledge from different subjects, fields and cultures, we open up for new ideas and create new opportunities for long-term sustainable societal development. Linnaeus University – where people grow.
Linnaeus University is running various national and European projects that focus on both fundamental and applied research. The Linnaeus University Centre for Data Intensive Sciences and Applications – DISA (www.lnu.se/en/disa) addresses data-driven methods to gain deeper knowledge and understanding in a variety of applications in engineering, science, and humanities. Linnaeus University runs a graduate school for industrial doctoral students that focuses on applied research, addressing the big data and artificial intelligence challenges of our industry partners.
The advertised positions will be placed at the department of Computer Science and Media Technology and work within the DISA High-Performance Computing Center (https://lnu.se/en/hpcc/). They will be affiliated with the research group on Data Intensive Software Technologies and Applications – DISTA (https://lnu.se/en//dista/) that studies data-driven approaches, such as machine learning, artificial intelligence, and big data, to automate and improve software development. DISTA is a core research area within DISA.
The advertised positions are part of a project that focuses on supporting small and medium sized companies that want to learn more about data-driven development and high-performance computing.
Field of subject for the position: Computer Science with specialization in Data-driven development and High-Performance Computing
Placement: Department of Computer Science and Media Technology, Faculty of Technology – Växjö Campus, Sweden
Employment: 100% employments, 2 positions full-time for two years with possibility for 1-year extension. At most 20% time can be dedicated to teaching and other departmental tasks
Start date: According to agreement
Job description and duties:
The position is focused on applied research in (Deep) Machine Learning and High-Performance Computing in collaboration with small and medium-sized companies (SMEs) in the Växjö and Kalmar regions. The research is guided by pilot cases, where the postdoc fellow works with an SME to find solutions to real-world problems. These real-world problems can be in different domains, such as software development, e-health, forestry, or industry 4.0.
The postdoc fellow is also expected to help educate the SMEs about the possibilities of data-driven technologies and high-performance computing and help guide them in their efforts to, e.g., improve how they work with or manage data or help scale their computing platform.
To the extent of maximal 20% of the working time, the postdoc fellow will be involved in teaching activities at different levels (incl. supervision of Bachelor’s and Master’s thesis projects). The teaching tasks relate to subjects of the DISTA research group, as well as to more general courses in computer science and software development.
The postdoc fellow is expected to regularly present intermediate/final research results at international conferences and workshops and publish them in conference proceedings and journals.
Eligibility Requirements:
Eligible to be employed are those who have completed a doctoral degree in Computer Science or an equivalent degree. The doctorate shall have been obtained no longer than three years before the expiration date of the application.
Eligibility for this position also requires that the doctoral thesis has a focus on (Deep) Machine Learning, High-Performance Computing, or similar, applied in one or more application areas.
Excellent written and oral communication skills in English are required and Swedish is a plus.
Assessment criteria:
Excellent knowledge in the applied research areas of (Deep) Machine Learning and High-Performance Computing is a must. Good programming skills in relevant languages (e.g., Python, C++, Julia) and project management skills are strong advantages. We value hands-on experience with commonly used technologies, such as Linux, containers and orchestration platforms, the most common machine learning frameworks and workflows, etc.
Teaching experiences in the related fields are a plus. Teamwork and good pedagogic skills are a must since a lot of the work with be conducted in collaboration with SME from the region Kalmar and Växjö. Documented expertise and working experience within at least one of the following research and educational areas is of great advantage:
Machine learning and statistics,
Big data analytics,
High-Performance Computing
Data-driven business/product development
Application of these technologies in more than one different area, e.g., in e-health, industry, forestry.
Excellent written and oral communication skills in English are required. Swedish skills are a plus. Teamwork experiences should also be documented in the application. Since the subject is male dominated, we encourage female applicants.
Applicants will be selected through a qualitative overall assessment of the competences and skills, assessed most suitable to conduct research and to contribute to the successful development of the research environment.
Further information Please contact:
Head of research, Prof. Welf Löwe, +46 470 708495, welf.lowe@lnu.se
Head of department, Assoc.-Prof. Morgan Ericsson, +46 470 767872, morgan.ericsson@lnu.se
Human Resources Consultant, Emmy Andersson, +46 480 446108 emmy.andersson@lnu.se
Welcome with your application before February 10th, 2023
Linnaeus University has the ambition to utilize the qualities that an even gender distribution and diversity brings to the organization.

Please apply by clicking on the Apply button at the bottom of the ad. Your application should be designed according to the Template for application which can be found in the Guide to Appointment procedures under important documents below the ad. The credentials you invoke must be verified with certification and they must be attached digitally in your application. Other documents, including various types of scientific works, must be submitted digitally along with the application. The application and other documents to be marked with the reference number. All documents cited must be received by the University no later than 24.00 (Local time in Sweden) on the closing day.


Länk till den här sidan
https://lnu.se/mot-linneuniversitetet/Lediga-jobb/?rmpage=job&rmjob=7022&rmlang=SE

Title: Data Warehouse Developer Wanted at ICA Banken
Description:
Are you an experienced ETL Engineer looking for a new challenge? ICA Banken is seeking a skilled Data Warehouse Developer to join our team and work on our MS SQL-based Data Warehouse and ETL solutions. As a member of our Data Management team, you will work alongside 10 senior experts in projects and proactive maintenance to provide data-driven insights to business stakeholders and end-users.
ETL Engineering in a Transforming Platform
In this role, you will play a vital role in the entire process for design, development, and operations of a traditional Data Warehouse system. You will focus on ETL data flows, but also align data needs with staff working with reporting, visualization and analysis. You will additionally contribute to ICA Banken’s new transformation initiative for implementing modern capabilities for advanced analytics on a cloud platform.

Key Responsibilities include:
Identify and analyze source data to meet business requirements
Design and develop Data Warehouse data models and structures
Design and develop ETL procedures and architectures
SQL programming of system components
Perform incident and error handling for the Data Warehouse system in production

We are looking for you
We believe you have solid experience in data warehousing and willing to excel in a Data warehouse developer position. You have an engineering background or similar with SQL experience. Both Swedish and English skills are preferred. This role can be located at ICA Bankens HQ in Borås or at the office in Solna.

Apply now
Any kind of questions about the position contact hiring manager Johan Karlsson, Manager Data Analytics +4610 422 02 28, questions about the selection process or terms & conditions at ICA please contact recruiter Markus Koppari, +4672 220 28 31 or Markus Öhman +4676 695 62 04. Apply as soon as possible, but no later than. 2023-02-19.

About ICA Banken
We are an everyday bank that lasts longer. We create personal, simple and affordable services for the ICA customer. Every day. Our business concept is to make everyday life a little easier for ICA's customers through financial services, as well as increase customers’ loyalty to ICA and reduce the ICA stores' and ICA AB's transaction costs for foreign banks and credit cards.
During this recruitment process we will use online tools for your safety for interviews and getting to know your skills. We also apply drug testing and control of credit information before all new hires.
Öppen för alla
Vi fokuserar på din kompetens, inte dina övriga förutsättningar. Vi är öppna för att anpassa rollen eller arbetsplatsen efter dina behov.

Title: Ikano Bank – B2B Decision Engineer
Description:
Do you have experience from working with financial product and B2B credit scoring models? Would you like to join Ikano Bank in a brand new position and be a part of their transformation journey? Then this might be the role for you!
Let´s create Finance solutions for a better living!
The role
As B2B Decision Engineer at Ikano Bank you will be involved in developing B2B scoring and policy rules for various product across the B2B markets. You will participate actively in Ikano Bank´s transformation journey and be the subject matter expert for B2B credit vetting and onboarding.
Preferred location is Malmö or Stockholm, but for the right candidate there is a possibility to be placed at one of Ikano Banks´s other offices. You will report to the Chief Credit Officer.
Tasks and responsibilities:
Ensure Ikano Bank´s B2B scorecards support the bank´s strategic targets
Measure the development of KPI´s related to onboarding, product performance, late payments
Proactively suggest new approaches to scoring and policy rules
Develop KRI´s and KPI´s in co-operation with Product, Risk Analytics, Finance, Sales teams
In co-operation with external data providers, ensure that external information related to customer onboarding is used optimally
Develop internal data and reporting
Scanning the credit environment, and ensuring that Ikano´s processes are relevant and up to-date
Participate in various projects within the bank´s B2B business
Are you the one for Ikano?
To be successful in this position we believe you have at least 3 years of relevant experience from a similar role. You have good knowledge of different financial products and B2B scoring models. You have excellent analytical skills, are well-structured and have a good stress tolerance. You are an independent person with a team player mind set and a hands-on approach. You hold a University degree in Business Administration, engineering or similar.You are fluent in English, both verbal and written, and have good knowledge in other Nordic languages.
How to apply
Ikano Bank collaborates with Academic Search International. For more questions about this role, please contact Senior Consultant Marcus Kleine, at marcus.kleine@academicsearch.se or +46 (0)736 50 31 77 or Senior Recruitment Manager Emma Herrlin at emma.herrlin@academicsearch.se or +46 (0)704 32 28 75.
You apply by clicking on the ”Apply now” button below, where you enter your personal details, enclose CV and cover letter. All information is handled confidentially in accordance with Academic Search Integrity Policy as well as the new data protection act, GDPR. This means that we can only process applications coming through the applications system. Thank you for your understanding.
About us Ikano Bank
Ikano Bank creates possibilities for better living by offering simple, fair and affordable services, enabling a healthy economy for the many people. Our offer includes savings and loan products for consumers, sales support services for retailers, and leasing and factoring solutions for businesses. We conduct business in Sweden, Denmark, Finland, Norway, the UK, Poland, Germany and Austria. Ikano Bank is a part of the Ikano Group, an international group of companies active within banking, real estate, production, insurance, data analytics and retail, who owns 51 % of the Bank. Ingka Group, a strategic partner in the IKEA franchise system, operating 378 IKEA stores in 31 countries, owns the remaining 49 % of Ikano Bank. Ikano Bank’s head office is located in Malmö, Sweden and the company is registered in Älmhult, Sweden where the business was once founded.
Please note that Ikano bank will perform credit check and request an extract from the criminal records as part of the pre-employment screening.
If Ikano discovers adverse credit in your name or should our investigations identify any other criminal offence by you (on your part) this may result in failure of the pre-employment screening. Failure to pass the above checks will result in an offer of employment being withdrawn. Please therefore contact the HR Department if you are concerned about any of the above or feel that there is any reason that you may not pass the above checks, contact HR at HRSupport.IKBAB@ikano.se, if you have any queries.
About Academic Search International
Academic Search International is one of Scandinavia’s most merited companies within Executive Search & Interim Management. Our focus is people with documented manager- and specialist competences. We have close collaborations with national and international companies with strong brands and purpose. Our mission is to unite the best qualified candidates with the toughest challenges at the most interesting companies in Sweden. Our values are KNOWLEDGE, ENGAGEMENT, RESPONSIBILITY and COLLABORATION. Through these values, we make a difference in all our relationships. Read more at www.academicsearch.se

Title: Juniora konsulter till EY Technology Consulting i Stockholm, Göteborg och Malmö
Description:
Vill du arbeta som managementkonsult med globala möjligheter och ny teknik i en inkluderande kultur? EY Technology Consulting söker dig som har tagit eller tar examen under 2022/2023 och som vill starta din karriär hos oss som techkonsult.
På EY får du chansen att bygga en karriär som är lika unik som du. Vi stödjer din resa mot att bli ditt bästa professionella jag. EY Consulting erbjuder dig som nyutexaminerad en strukturerad metod för utbildning och coachning genom vårt unika SPOT ON-program. Genom SPOT ON ges du möjlighet att uppnå din fulla potential, stöttas i en säker inlärningsmiljö, vara del av utvecklande interna projekt och roller samtidigt som du bygger ett internationellt nätverk. Vi räknar med din röst och ditt perspektiv för att hjälpa oss att bli ännu bättre. Bli en del av EY och bygg en unik upplevelse för dig själv och en bättre affärsvärld för alla.
Vår rådgivningsverksamhet inom Consulting är indelad i tre områden: Business Consulting, Technology Consulting och People Consulting. Varje område är i sin tur indelade i ett antal undergrupperingar med mer specifik kompetens. Inom vår Financial Services Organisation (FSO) som finns representerad inom Business Consulting och Technology Consulting arbetar vi fokuserat med kunder inom finansbranschen; bank, försäkring samt kapitalförvaltning. Inom Consultings verksamhet arbetar vi branschbrett, mot flera olika sektorer.

Möjligheten
Som konsult hos oss inom EY Technology Consulting kommer du att delta i förändringsprogram och hjälpa våra kunder att identifiera, utveckla och implementera mätbara och hållbara förbättringar med fokus på digitalisering, teknologi och IT. På EY är vi övertygade om att hållbarhet skapar möjligheter till innovation. Företag och människor är mer benägna än någonsin tidigare att samarbeta för att påskynda en mer hållbar framtid. Tillsammans kan vi skapa långsiktigt värde för konsumenter, människor, samhällen och alla intressenter. Du kommer arbeta med en mängd olika kunder från nystartade företag till välkända organisationer och utifrån problematik definiera strategier och lösningar. I arbetet ingår även att analysera trender inom olika branscher.

Dina huvudsakliga arbetsområden
Inom EY finns stora utvecklingsmöjligheter och du kommer att få utmanande och utvecklande uppdrag med spridning avseende både marknadssegment, bransch och företag. Inom Consulting jobbar vi i blandade team och samarbetar mellan våra olika områden för att säkerställa bred kompetens och flera infallsvinklar. Då EY är ett internationellt företag med många globala kunder finns det även möjlighet att arbeta utomlands och i internationella projekt.
Nedan följer några exempel på arbetsområden som vi inom våra grupper Technology Transformation, Data & Analytics, Digital & Emerging Technology och Technology Solution Delivery arbetar med och som du kommer att få möjligheten att utvecklas inom:
Utveckling av strategi, organisation och styrning samt effektivisering av verksamhetsprocesser med digitalisering i centrum
Projektleda och säkerställa implementering av såväl mindre digitaliseringsinitiativ till stora transformations- och förändringsprogram ofta genom agila metoder
Arbete i och med såväl nya som etablerade teknikområden såsom RPA, Digitala arbetsplatslösningar, AR och affärssystem inom olika plattformar (exempelvis SAP och Microsoft)
Sätta upp och konfigurera systemlösningar samt anpassa lösningar till kundens behov
Designa och implementera operativa modeller, sourcingstrategier och partnerskap mellan leverantörer och beställare
Designa, analysera och implementera IT-arkitektur och strategier
Stötta kunder med att genomföra nuläges- och framtidsanalyser
Rådgivning av den potentiella affärsnyttan med digitaliseringsinitiativ
Internt arbete som att delta i produktutveckling, intern analys, teambuilding, rekrytering och säljarbete

Vad vi söker
Vi söker individer med olika bakgrunder och infallsvinklar som vill vara med och stötta våra kunder kring förbättringar och risker i den snabba utveckling och förändring som de befinner sig i. I våra team ser vi gärna individer med goda studieresultat från olika typer av utbildningar såsom: civilingenjörer, systemvetare, affärssystem och ekonomer med ett intresse av att lära dig mer om digitalisering, IT och ny teknik. Vi söker dig som delar våra värderingar och som:
Uppskattar att arbeta i team och har förmågan att bygga långsiktiga relationer med kollegor såväl som kunder
Har en proaktiv inställning, är nyfiken och har förmåga att driva dig själv framåt
Kan hantera förändring och att arbeta i en föränderlig vardag
Har en stark analytisk förmåga och uppskattar att lösa komplexa problem
Trivs med ett högt arbetstempo och uppskattar en varierad arbetssituation
Har intresse för hur nya trender och ny teknik kan driva förändring av företags affärsmodell

För att kvalificera dig behöver du
Relevant universitetsexamen (Mastersnivå eller relevant kandidatexamen)
Framstående akademiska meriter
0–3 års arbetslivserfarenhet efter avlagd examen
Erfarenheter från arbetsliv/föreningsliv/förtroendeuppdrag vid sidan av dina studier
Kommunicera obehindrat i tal och skrift, både på svenska och engelska

Vad EY erbjuder dig
Kontinuerligt lärande: Du utvecklar tankesätt och färdigheter som hjälper dig att navigera in i framtiden.
Framgång så som du definierar den: Vi ger dig verktygen och flexibiliteten, så att du kan göra skillnad på ditt sätt.
Transformativt ledarskap: Vi ger dig insikter, coachning och självförtroende för att bli den ledare som världen behöver.
Inkluderande kultur: Du kommer att accepteras för den du är och få möjlighet att använda din röst för att hjälpa andra att hitta sin.
SPOT ON: som nyutexaminerad konsult kommer du att få vara en del av vårt unika onboarding program SPOT-ON där du snabbt får utbildas inom och praktisera rollen som konsult i en trygg miljö.
Läs gärna mer om EY på EY Careers och vad våra kollegor säger om sin vardag inom Consulting samt på Karriärbloggen, och i sociala medier EY Sweden Careers (@eysecareers) • Instagram photos and videos

The exceptional EY experience. It’s yours to build.

Ansökan
EY erbjuder ett antal karriärvägar och möjligheter med många alternativ och vi förstår att det kan vara svårt att välja. Vi kommer vägleda dig genom rekryteringsprocessen för att du ska kunna finna just det området som passar dina intressen och kunskapsprofil allra bäst.
Är du mer intresserad av att arbeta inom några av våra andra områden inom Consulting? Kolla in Business- och People Consulting, Financial Services Organization och Cyber Security. På Karriär inom konsulttjänster (ey.com) kan du även läsa mer om våra grupper inom respektive område.

Välkommen med din ansökan där du bifogar CV, personligt brev samt betyg från högskola/universitet och gymnasium. Vi uppskattar om du kan sammanfoga dessa tre filer i ett och samma dokument. Notera att du behöver ladda upp samtliga angivna dokument för att din ansökan ska anses fullständig. Du kommer inom ett par dagar motta ett online-test som vi ser att du genomför snarast. Efter testet sker urval och inbjudande till intervjuer löpande. Under rekryteringsprocessen kommer vi att vara nyfikna på att veta mer om dig, varför du har valt att söka dig till EY och du kommer få lära känna oss. Läs mer om vår rekryteringsprocess på Karriärmöjligheter för nyutexaminerade (ey.com)
Urval och intervjuer sker löpande och vi ser därför gärna att du ansöker snarast, dock senast 28 februari 2023. Har du frågor kring rekryteringsprocessen är du välkommen att kontakta amanda.hederstedt@se.ey.com.
Välkommen med din ansökan!

At EY we celebrate differences and support it. Our employees bring their authentic selves to work every day. We promote diversity of thought, culture and background, and are committed to creating an inclusive EY environment for all employees. EY is an equal opportunity employer for employees and applicants. EY encourages applications from all backgrounds related to gender, age, ethnicity, culture, race, religion and belief, nationality, disability, sexual orientation and gender identity.
If you need assistance or an accommodation due to a disability in your recruitment process, you may contact us through the Talent Attraction and Acquisition specialist in this advert.

EY | Building a better working world

EY exists to build a better working world, helping to create long-term value for clients, people and society and build trust in the capital markets.

Enabled by data and technology, diverse EY teams in over 150 countries provide trust through assurance and help clients grow, transform and operate.

Working across assurance, consulting, law, strategy, tax and transactions, EY teams ask better questions to find new answers for the complex issues facing our world today.

Title: Regional Account Executive, Nordics
Description:
Amplitude is a leading digital analytics platform. More than 1,900 customers, including Atlassian, Jersey Mike's, Marks & Spencer, NBCUniversal, PayPal, Shopify, and Under Armour rely on Amplitude to gain self-service visibility into the entire customer journey. With Amplitude, teams can understand what product features are working, where users are getting stuck, and what actions lead to the right outcomes. As an organization, we approach challenges with humility, take ownership of our contributions, and embrace a growth mindset that pushes us to constantly improve ourselves, each other, and the value we bring to customers and partners.
Amplitude's Commitment to Diversity Equity & Inclusion (DEI): Amplitude believes that diversity enables creation of better products, ability to solve complex problems, and drive more powerful solutions. In order to make diversity possible, we commit to striving to create an environment of inclusion: an environment focused on psychological safety, empathy, and human connection, which will allow employees of all backgrounds to feel the care they need to thrive.
About The Role & Team
Our North EMEA Region is looking to hire our next dedicated Regional Account Executive for the Nordics market. We've built a great cross-functional team for this market and are looking to continue to build upon that success this year - so this is an exciting opportunity to join the team as we scale post our debut on the Nasdaq, and look to increase momentum and market maturity.
As a NordicsRegional AE, you will:
Create new opportunities in all segments with a focus on corporate and enterprise clients through prospecting, networking, etc. Primary focus is to land new logos in the region.

Title: Master Data Engineer (f/m/d)
Description:
Master Data Engineer (f/m/d)
We strongly believe that in this digital age for a sustainable competitiveness it is imperative to have a strong focus on Data & Analytics cutting across Business Services. In this role of Master Data Engineer, you will work across various Data & Analytics Tools, Applications, and Big Data Platforms. You feel ownership (and are responsible) for the master data, as key company asset and driving, govern, and guide teams and know how to maximise value and balance speed and quality in delivery. You are aware about the best practices in Data & Analytics domain and you know the best way to utilise them or you are keen to learn and share your findings with others. As part of the Analytics Microsoft Delivery team you will be working closely with Data Analytics Project teams, Data Science, Enterprise Architecture, and Business Unit teams to contribute towards the data strategy; as well as with Application Architects and Solution Architects to implement coherent solution architecture and learn from each other.
We’re looking for people who embody our values, aren’t afraid to challenge, innovate, experiment, and move at a fast pace. We’re always looking for ways to improve our products and ourselves. If this is you, we’d love to talk.
What You Will Do

Align and implement measures to ensure data accuracy and accessibility
Constantly monitor, refine, and report on the performance of data management systems
Implement system configuration changes based on defined solution
Ensure that developed solutions are peer reviewed and formally documented according to company IT standards
Unit test solutions to ensure that they meet quality standards
Maintain, support and repair solutions to ensure performance in accordance with technical and functional specification
Cooperate with other data engineers to make sure that the applications meet requirements and performance goals
Who You Are University degree in computer science, management information systems, or related discipline
More than five years of application programming (python or Scala) and ETL/ELT experience
More than two years working with big data technologies including Hadoop, Apache Spark
More than two years working experience with Databricks and Microsoft Azure Data Lake tools (Azure Data Lake, Azure Databricks, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Warehouse, Power BI, Logic Apps)

Expert in a combination of Spark (Python, R or Scala), PySpark, Spark SQL, Pandas, and/or Spark Streaming
Advanced knowledge of Python to be able to perform code refactoring
Experience with enterprise master data systems and concepts is a plus

Title: Senior Data Governance Engineer (m/f/d)
Description:
Everything we do, starts with you.
Together with you, we build the most human-centric fintech. We have the ambition to create the next. And - with Bertelsmann - a strong foundation to start from. Let’s make it new – for society and for yourself.

Riverty offers customers payment solutions that make everyday life simpler!

Our solutions contribute to a flexible and customer-friendly payment alternative, offering customers (m/f/d) the opportunity to choose when and how they want to pay for a purchase. Delivering a trustworthy and positive shopping experience, both for retailers and end customers makes us proud but not content. Our ambition is higher and now we have a great opportunity for a Data Governance Engineer (m/f/d) to join our growing team.

We are looking for a
Senior Data Governance Engineer (m/f/d)
(unlimited, full-time) in Berlin, Stockholm, Amsterdam, Oslo, Tallinn, Baden-Baden or Verl with 80% Mobile Office

to enable data driven business insights while adhering to all compliance guidelines globally to seamlessly deliver best-in-class consumer applications across our streaming properties.

This role requires acute attention to detail, a strong sense of accountability, collaboration and understanding of large-scale cloud data platform infrastructure. In this role you will work directly with analytics, data architecture, and data engineering stakeholders to ensure our data ecosystem maintains the highest standards for data quality across our global footprint.

What You Will Do
Support data quality roadmaps, strategy, and procedures for adhering to facilitate data lifecycle management and data stewardship best practices with a focus on improvement of data quality, common understanding, and the protection of sensitive data through modifications to governance metrics, processes, related tools, and data architecture.
Participate in discussions with business and data stakeholders globally to ensure clarity, consistency, understanding and adoption of standard definitions for business metrics and KPI’s.
Assist in compliance audits for key issues related to GDPR, PII, legal guidance, and other financial regulations.
Serve as an interface between data stakeholders across the organization to ensure alignment, communication and understanding of new and evolving definitions for business metrics and KPI’s.
Develop, implement and document data policies, standards, and procedures for new data environments as well as for data quality including data catalogs, etc.
Develop and deliver data quality training across the organization including the implementation of quality-oriented controls and frameworks.
Help to optimize the data security systems in accordance with the company's data protection policy, applicable legal requirements, and security policies.

What You Should Bring
At least 5 years of experience in large-scale Data & Analytics solutions with relevant experience in defining and implementing data governance and quality best practices, documenting data flow & process mapping, or a data steward responsible for the metadata management, data quality KPIs, etc.
Experience working with regulatory compliance frameworks such as GDPR and CCPA.
Extensive experience and knowledge of data governance strategies, data quality and data protection management practices.
Expertise in risk data architecture and technology solutions, and experience creating data glossaries.
Strong communication skills and the ability to explain processes or choices as needed to stakeholders.
Technical knowledge of modern data governance concepts, data modelling and data management.
Hands-on experience in Microsoft Azure technology stack (Synapse, Analysis Services, SQLDB, ADLS2, Power BI) and data catalog tools like Purview.
Excellent English language skills, German is a plus.
Exceptional initiative and strong analytical thinking with a problem-solving attitude.
Ability to drive innovation and to solve complex tasks in a dynamic and challenging environment.
Possess the ability to balance multiple priorities in an agile team.
You are a team player.

This would get us excited but the lack experience of shouldn´t keep you from applying:
Experience with the financial industry, especially in Buy Now, Pay Later and Debt Collection.
Experience with Purview.

Here we have a few arguments for you! This is why you should join our great workforce!
At Riverty, we offer you modern workplace models with 80% Mobile Office globally. For more flexibility and freedom.
With us, life balance is not just something we claim, but something we live, and you can do the same in many European countries where we are operating. Riverty helps you to arrange your working life in the way that suits you best. Big city or small town? You can choose to work remotely and still stay connected with your team virtually. And if it gets too quiet at home, you can just drop by our tech hubs in Berlin and Tallinn, or any of our 13 locations across Europe.
At Riverty, we are as diverse as society itself. We have great people from more than 25 different countries around the world - creating the most human-centric fintech together. With us, you can be who you are.
Culture? Easy: Open and at eye level, trust instead of dislike, cooperation instead of lone warriors. You will work in cross-functional, agile, dynamic teams with a start-up spirit. At the same time, you will benefit from all the opportunities within the Bertelsmann Group.
Take time for yourself and your health. With sports and leisure activities we support your wellbeing.
We want to grow together. With trainings from the Riverty Academy and individual training opportunities we support your development.
Because we appreciate what you do. For us. For our customers. Check our many employee discounts. To sweeten your everyday life.

About Riverty: Who we are
A world where business meets the needs of humanity. Where financial technology makes a difference. Where everyone is in control of their own financial story. At Riverty, we’re building it, together. A team of more than 5,000 experts in 13 countries, we’re finding smarter, simpler, seamlessly connected ways to manage money. From flexible payments to smarter accounting and debt collection, our holistic solutions empower everyone to live their best financial lives. It’s time to enter a new era of economic freedom.

Title: HPC specialist
Description:
The EuroCC National Competence Center Sweden (ENCCS) is looking for a researcher with a background in natural sciences or data science / machine learning and extensive experience in high performance computing (HPC). ENCCS is a national competence center in HPC, funded by the Swedish Research Council, Vinnova and the EuroHPC JU via the EuroCC project - a network of European national competence centers in HPC. ENCCS is hosted jointly by RISE and Linköping University.
EuroHPC JU is a multi-billion Euro joint undertaking which enables participating countries to coordinate their efforts and share resources in order to build a world-class supercomputing infrastructure and a competitive innovation ecosystem in supercomputing technologies, applications, and skills in Europe.
ENCCS provides a range of services tailored to the national needs of industry, academia, and public administration in Sweden. The aim is to support and further enhance national strengths in high-performance computing (HPC), high-performance data analytics (HPDA), and artificial intelligence (AI). The specific objectives of ENCCS are to:
Develop expertise, knowledge, and support in Sweden to help users make better use of EuroHPCresources.
Assist key user communities in enabling applications on (pre)exa-scale resources.
Advise users on how to achieve scaling and performance for scientific problems on EuroHPC resources.
Guide new industrial users in using HPC.
Support new AI/data analytics applications. Provide training and skill development nationally and throughout Europe.
About the role
You will be working with an agile team of experts with diverse backgrounds and a shared passion for bringing the benefits of HPC to new user groups through teaching and mentoring, awareness creation, consulting and hands-on software support. Specifically, the work includes supporting users in moving to (pre)exa-scale EuroHPC systems, porting and/or optimizing scientific software for HPC in pilot projects as well as teaching workshops and developing training material. The researcher will also contribute to the development and implementation of the ENCCS strategy, including the development of the service portfolio, establishing collaborations and identifying new user communities.
Please note that this position may mean that a security clearance is required, either later in this process or in the future.
About you
A PhD in natural sciences, data science, machine learning or related areas.
Experience in software development for HPC systems.
Experience with GPU programming.
Excellent communication skills in English and (preferably) Swedish.
Strong communication and team working skills. Teaching experience is a plus.
What We Offer
RISE offers an inclusive workplace with a dynamic environment that gives you opportunities for development both professionally and personally. You will work in a team of committed colleagues to tackle exciting societal challenges. If you are an experienced researcher with a background in HPC and have excellent communication skills, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity!
Welcome with your application!
Please submit your application via the form above. For any questions, please contact Thor Wikfeldt (thor.wikfeldt@ri.se or +46 10 228 4679). Last day of application i January 31, 2023. Please not, we do not accept any applications via email.

Title: Power BI konsult
Description:
Motiveras du av att få möjligheten av att arbeta med kolleger som har kaliber inom sitt område och samtidigt ta del av spännande uppdrag hos våra kunder? Just nu söker vi dig som vill arbeta i rollen som BI – utvecklare hos oss med några års erfarenhet inom Power BI.
Till vår avdelning AI/BI/Database Development i Stockholm söker vi dig som nu är redo för ditt nästa steg och vill vara med på vår resa med att växa internationellt.
Varför börja arbeta hos oss?
Hos oss på Sysco/SQL Service arbetar branschens bästa inom SQL Server.
SYSCO/SQL Service är ett bolag med fokus på Data management och Data Analytics. Vi levererar konsulttjänster inom alla branscher, men även support och drifttjänster.
Våra medarbetare är stolta och passionerade över sitt arbete. Hos oss får du jobba med några av de bästa databaskonsulterna i Sverige och får möjligheten att accelerera din kompetensökning.
Om rollen
Utveckling / BI - teamet hos SQL Service består av ett gäng erfarna och dedikerade SQL och BI utvecklare som alla brinner för Data management och Data Analytics. Vi jobbar oftast med utveckling av databaser, ETL flöden, Power BI rapporter och Data Warehouse lösningar på SQL Server on-premise och i Azure. Vi blir också ofta involverade i prestandaanalyser, databasarkitektur frågor, dekryptering av databaser och DevOps frågor.
Vi stöttar även vårt Support team med utveckling av deras övervakningsplattform baserat på de senaste Azure teknologierna.
I rollen som BI – konsult kommer du få möjligheten att jobba med att omsätta verksamhetskrav till datamodeller och dashboards i framförallt Power BI. En stor del av jobbet handlar mest om att utveckla kod för att extrahera, transformera och ladda data till modeller som du skapat.
Om dig
Du är en person som drivs av att lära dig nya saker och därför stimuleras av att vara ute hos våra kunder i konsultuppdrag. Att ligga i framkant är för dig självklart och du delar gärna med dig av dina erfarenheter och din kunskap till andra. Du är initiativrik , självständig och analytisk. Som BI-utvecklare och konsult hos oss kommer du erbjudas en central roll i projekten hos våra kunder där du kommer att få chansen att göra stor skillnad. Att ha ett konsultmässigt förhållningssätt är för dig en självklarhet och du drivs av att lösa problem på given deadline.
Vi ser gärna att du har erfarenhet av följande:
2-3 års erfarenhet av utveckling av data warehouse i MSSQL miljö
2-3 års erfarenhet av utveckling i Power BI
SSAS Tabular
T-SQL eller motsvarande
ETL verktyg som exempelvis SSIS och Azure Data Factory
Det är meriterande om:
du har erfarenhet av QlikView/Tableu/SSRS/Crystal Reports
du har erfarenhet av Azure DataLake/ Azure Data Factory
du har erfarenhet av Azure Databricks/ Databricks/Apache Spark
du har erfarenhet av Python/R/Scala
Vi vet att alla inte uppfyller våra punkter ovan men med rätt inställning och vilja så finns möjligheten att utvecklas hos oss då vi är ett prestigelöst gäng som gärna delar med oss av våra erfarenheter.
Vi har kunder inom många olika branscher och som verkar internationellt. Många av våra kunder är säkerhetsklassade arbetsplatser vilket innebär att vi i vissa fall behöver göra bakgrundskontroller och att du som anställd har ett svenskt medborgarskap. Vi ser även gärna att du behärskar svenska och engelska obehindrat.

Vad kan vi erbjuda dig?
Vi kan erbjuda dig kunskapsutbyte och utveckling tillsammans med kolleger som besitter lång och unik kunskap. Vi är även måna om att du ska må bra och att du i så stor utsträcknig som möjligt ska kunna påverka din vardag så att du kan arbeta både remote och ute hos kund. Vi värdesätter balans mellan jobb och fritid och åker ofta på gemensamma sammankomster och utbildningar tillsammans.
Vi erbjuder dig:
Goda möjligheter till att utvecklas i din kompetens i ett bolag som växer på ett internationellt plan
Sociala sammankomster och kontinuerlig utbildning
Prestigelös kultur, stor frihet och en miljö där vi har roligt tillsammans
Varierande och utvecklande konsultuppdrag inom olika branscher
Goda försäkringsförmåner

Interesserad?
Ta kontakt med Rekryteringsansvarig Eleonor Sjunnevik, eleonor@escoaching.se mobilnr +46 73 501 78 10

Välkommen med din ansökan!
