Work Location: Hybrid remote in Malmö

Title: Marketing - Influencer Manager- Trainee
Description:
Landell Games AB was established in 2021 and performs consulting work in IT such as infrastructure, due diligence, and the manufacture of software such as video games and innovative technology.
We are looking for several Influencer Manager interns that would join us for 6 months part-time or full-time with the opportunity to extend it further, and since we are in discussions with big names in the video game industry, we plan to start our recruitment process shortly.
It is important to note that the internship period is unpaid.
Our marketing department and its potential are growing rapidly and we are now looking for interns who can help us with various tasks, mostly focusing on analyzing and reaching out to analyzing and reaching out to influencers on social media and other platforms.
Your assignments would consist of analyzing influencers so that you could determine their reliability. Depending on provided parameters, you would make sure that the influencers we contact match our needs well and are able to help us reach more potential players and customers. You would also make sure that we know everything about their social media and other communities they might be a part of.
The most important attribute you need is a strong drive to learn and see things through, and if you are ready to put in sweat and tears, we are ready to provide you with a unique skill set that will help us reach our goals and help you build an impressive portfolio for your future endeavors in the gaming industry.
Examples of assignments:
Your assignments would consist of analyzing influencers so that you could determine their reliability and usefulness for our campaign. Depending on provided parameters, you would make sure that the influencers we contact match our needs well and help us acquire more potential players and customers. You would also make sure that we know everything about their social media and other communities they might be a part of.
- Analyzing the engagement rate of influencer accounts on various social media and learning about the platforms they might be using that we are not yet aware of
- Gathering emails of the influencers, writers and editors we need to contact
- Contacting influencers and making sure that they understand what we offer them and how they can best suit their content to promote our game
- Nurturing relationships with the contacted influencers and making sure that they follow through on their tasks and promotions
Who we are:
We pride ourselves on being hardworking, determined and passionate. Positive mindset and hunger for knowledge are in our blood and we are always happy to help each other out and welcome new members to the project. The team itself works together remotely and has many years of combined experience in the growing gaming industry and is growing by the day, with more than 30 gaming enthusiasts currently working on the project.
We are very open to sharing our knowledge and we encourage every member to be inquisitive about the methods and progress of their own team, as well as about the other departments. Voicing one's opinion is extremely important in our mission of game development and self betterment, so we see it as a quality of motivated individuals and welcome it on every occasion.
We offer you to:
- Shape your own way of working and choose your working hours with us
- Get the opportunity to learn from practical experience in Marketing, namely Data Analytics and Influncer Management
- Work on an ambitious project that you can use in your portfolio
- Learn about developing a game as a whole
- Make invaluable connections
- Have fun and hopefully make lifelong friendships
Who you are:
- First and foremost, a passionate gamer who sincerely wants an opportunity to work in the gaming industry
- An independent individual not afraid to ask questions, solve problems and address issues
- A creative, inquisitive and detail oriented person who is willing to make their own decisions and are genuinely excited to learn and develop their knowledge within marketing in gaming industry
Requirements:
- Fluency in English
- Basic understanding of Excel and/or Google sheets
- Willingness and ability to dedicate at least 10 hours a week to the project for the period of at least 6 months
Additional (not required) skills:
- Experience with influencer management
- Experience with promotion gaming content on social media
- Experience with previous Kickstarter Campaigns
- Basic understanding of Social Media insights and analytics
Read more about the game project at: https://DawnofEmpires.com
Attach your Resume/CV together with a short description of why you would be the best fit for us.
We are looking forward to getting to know you better!

Arbetstider:
Måndag till fredag

Svenskkunskap krävs inte

Title: Senior Data Engineer - Technical Lead
Description:
Oneflow is a rapidly growing tech scale-up located in the heart of Stockholm. We have created a platform that automates the entire contract process from start to finish, all in one place. Turning clunky, static contracts into helpful, truly digital contracts that feel like magic.
With strategic goals to become a more data-driven organization and focusing on Product-Led Growth, we are now looking for a Senior Data Engineer who will help us shape our data warehouse strategy, lead the data engineering team and build the data ecosystem that will serve as a one-stop shop for the needs of the entire organization.
Who you are
You are an experienced Data Engineer who knows the SaaS space well. You’re familiar with the data analytics needs of a modern technology company as well as how to realize them.
You have a structured approach to your team’s work, delivering iteratively while keeping the company’s strategic goals and the users’ needs in mind. You are an effective communicator that has experience leading a technical team, acting as the go-to person within your area of expertise and creating a culture of continuous improvement, curiosity and innovation.
What you'll do
Together with the data engineering team, you will architect, implement and maintain data pipelines feeding data from various sources into our data warehouse
Ensure the data warehouse is performant and scalable as needed with support from data engineers
Collaborate with product developers and data scientists to deliver new data features and enable the discovery of insights
Collaborate with data scientists to ensure our data warehouse always contains high-quality data
Act as a technical and architectural lead for the data engineering team

Skills and requirements
A proven background working in the data engineering field
Experience with architectural choices, configurations, and tradeoffs related to the data ecosystem of a modern technology company
Ability to think strategically while iteratively implementing solutions based on the immediate needs of an agile organization
Experience designing data models that enable long-term stability, maintainability and scalability of a data warehouse
Prior experience as a technical team lead, coaching and growing individuals is highly beneficial

What’s in it for you
Joining a high-growth scale up with a clear vision, objectives, and key results
Fast-paced, fun, and open work culture
Yearly healthcare benefit of 5000 SEK
Snacks in the office every day
Weekly/monthly culture based activities
Insurance and pension plan
Highly skilled and inspiring international colleagues
Leave your mark, create your own career path

Come work with us
We value gender equality and diversity in organization, so we strive for a team that reflects the diversity in today's society. Our recruitment is based on competence.
The recruitment process starts with an interview with Emese from the Talent Acquisition. After that, you will complete a personality and logic test, then prepare an assignment before your final interview with Fadi, Kalle and Alex.
Apply by submitting your CV and a personal letter about why this is the role for you. We can’t wait to meet you!
Visit our website for more information about our product and Oneflow. Visit our blog for more information about our culture and future colleagues.

Title: Senior IT Business Partner
Description:
IT Business Performance Manager
Macclesfield, Luton (UK) Gothenburg (Sweden) Gaithersburg, Wilmington (USA)
JOB ROLE
The Senior Business Partner works closely with Senior Stakeholders providing functional planning and performance management services as well as driving transformation change. They develop strategic management plans and lead transformation initiatives, whilst running performance measurement processes linking strategic objectives to key performance indicators, to drive the delivery of IT2025 and improve the overall performance of the function and IT as a whole.
Technology at AstraZeneca is a home for purposeful disruptors!
Here our work has a direct impact on patients – transforming our ability to develop life-changing medicines. We empower the business to perform at its peak and lead a new way of working, combining cutting-edge science with leading digital technology platforms and data. All with a passion to impact lives through data, analytics, AI, machine learning and more. In Business Partnering we will provide strategic partnership to the ITLT and the broader IT organisation. We will drive continuous improvement and alignment, as well as preparing the organisation to meet the needs of the future. As the Senior Business Partner you will report to the Director of Business Partnering in IT's Strategy & Performance function.
KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES
Be a trusted partner and advisor to a senior leadership team with the purpose to enable functions to accelerate delivery, work smarter and leaner
Enable the creation, delivery and execution of key Strategy & Performance deliverables (e.g. Strategy Cascade, Tier, Scorecard)
Support functional strategic planning, to enable organisations to become more future focussed, operationally efficient and aligned.
Be a strategic advisor to the ITLT to advise on Industry trends both inside and outside of AstraZeneca, that could help innovation and transformation.
Identify opportunities to improve the Service Offering of Strategy and Performance, or to help improve, standardise or transform the way that IT delivers.
Drive a continuous improvement mindset and foster culture of collaboration and partnership across both S&P and IT as a whole.
Align all the areas of Strategy and Performance so that there is a seamless customer interaction and shared information flow.
Create and design appropriate measures, evaluate metrics and outputs and report on business performance and trends so that ITLT understand business performance against key indicators, risks and actions to mitigate risks
Create and manage the scorecard creation for the functional leadership team, ensuring that the measures are aligned to the strategic business priorities and provide a realistic overview of business performance against targets
Support the implementation of Key IT Initiatives to drive organisational change and improve business performance.
Lead the development and implementation of solutions to problems identified through analysis and data driven insights
Communicate performance and trends to ITLT to identify risks at the earliest stage possible
WORKS COLLOBORATIVELY
Functional leadership as the key interface and source of management of business performance against key indicators, areas of risk, and actions to mitigate risk
Functional leadership and wider IT team to create and own a Performance Improvement approach and to drive the implementation of a performance management culture based on effective measurement & continuous improvement
ESSENTIAL SKILLS & EXPERIENCE
Progressive experience in Consulting, IT business or financial management
Progressive experience leading cross functional teams and building consensus and influencing senior stakeholders.
Demonstrated ability to lead change, transform organisational operations and drive alignment
Experience with benchmarking/scorecards and reporting
Strong skills using the suite of Microsoft Office products
DESIRABLE EXPERIENCE
Strong customer service orientation
Have an entrepreneurial mindset and search for new opportunities.

Title: Group Category Manager - Digital
Description:
In this exciting role you will lead, develop, and empower a knowledgeable team of professional buyers for indirect material – together we can reach our goal in scaling up Polestar.

Let us describe the challenge we offer
Polestar is aiming to bring driving pleasure into a new era with an all-electric product offering of progressive performance cars that are designed and engineered without compromise with minimized CO2 footprint. This will be combined with a hassle-free ownership and premium services, where all interactions and orders can be performed online.
We have an exciting new opportunity for a leader within Procurement. In this role you will lead, develop, and empower a knowledgeable team of professional buyers for indirect material – together we can reach our goal in scaling up Polestar.
As a Category Manager for Digital, you will have the responsibility to identify internal and external stakeholders and develop strategic alliances with them, provide the team with facilities to succeed in sustainable business relations with suppliers, TCO and TVO -guidance and participate actively as a team member and represent Procurement in new business development initiatives.
The main subcategories within Digital are:
Software.
Services
Hardware
Which mainly serve our Global Digital Organization structured as, Product Creation and Industrial, Commerce, Customer acquisition, data analytics, architecture and info Security ....
We believe that work-life balance is important, and of course, welcome our employees to work flexible hours and from home a couple of days per week. We believe in empowerment.
This role will report to Head of IDP, EMEA and is located at our HQ in Gothenburg, Sweden.


What you'll do
Together with a global procurement team you will work in close collaboration with stakeholders and oversee enhancement of running business and all sourcing activities for new business development projects.
Your main tasks will include:
Collaborate and be early involved with stakeholders to develop the supplier base to meet business needs
Co create Career Development Plan with your team and follow up the progress
Accountable for end-to-end deliveries of the category team including Strategy, Sourcing and contract negotiations
Accountable for Category Business Plan for dedicated Commodities
Coach your team for achieving sustainability goals, increased transparency & traceability, total cost of ownership (TCO), quality, on time delivery, and project objectives
Support the team to negotiate commercial contracts and agreements with business partners
Participate in BRMs (Business Review Meetings) with key business partners and suppliers
Establishing a new EV car brand for an exciting future , will require a lot of flexibility and creative thinking while keeping a strong integrity. You act proactively, with focus on the right thing and getting the job done.

Who you are
To succeed in this role we believe that exceptional communication skills, a strong inclusive leadership and a yes-can-do approach are key notes. You will also benefit from a smart and nimble mind-set and an efficient way of working to be able to perform.
Strong networking skills in a global environment, to build professional relationship
A mature team player
Strong English language skills in speaking and writing
Positive and passionate - nothing is impossible mind-set
Approx. 5 years+ procurement experience
3 years+ experience of developing and managing procurement team with direct reports, global team preferred
University degree in engineering, business management or equivalent
Familiar with global indirect material/ NAP supply base
A passion for sustainability and a determined mind to improve the society we live in will make you feel that you are in the right place together with us.
At Polestar, you will be part of a cross-functional and international team, with English as a natural language for written and spoken communication. Since Polestar’s in a scale-up phase you thrive by working in a fast-paced environment.

People at Polestar
We know that a change is needed. We also know that each one of us can help bring about that change. Our commitment to becoming climate-neutral by 2040 is just as important to us as being inclusive, diverse, and innovative. Together, we are creating, collaborating and experimenting to usher in a new era of sustainable mobility.
We are an electric performance brand, determined to improve the society we live in.

Is this you? If you are interested in joining the Polestar family, don't wait with submitting your application. We apply a continuous selection process and the job post will be open until the position is filled.

Are you ready for the journey? Which is electric by the way...

Title: Business Analyst
Description:
What makes Cognizant a unique place to work? The combination of rapid growth and an international and innovative environment! This is creating a lot of opportunities for people like YOU — people with an entrepreneurial spirit who want to make a difference in this world.
At Cognizant, together with your colleagues from all around the world, you will collaborate on creating solutions for the world's leading companies and help them become more flexible, more innovative and successful. And this is your chance to be part of the success story: we are looking for a consultant to join our AI & Analytics Advisory Team.

About Cognizant Artificial Intelligence and Analytics Advisory (AIA) Consulting
In the Nordic Artificial Intelligence and Analytics Advisory Consulting team at Cognizant Consulting, we have the dynamic and entrepreneurial freedom of a small organization, yet the professionalism and long-term sustainability of a large organization. We are a small Nordic practice with aggressive growth ambitions. As we belong to a Fortune 500 company with $16 billion in annual revenues, we provide strategic advice to clients on issues at the cusp of business and technology for latest next generation data & analytical solution. We provide and enhance a value proposition by helping clients tackle business problems with Data solutions. We are agile enough to engage with clients on their most strategic initiatives and have the knowhow and financial strength to deliver the most challenging change programmers. Our consulting practice is rated leader in current forester AI consulting firms. “Engineering Modern business to improve everyday life “is Cognizant’s agenda to solve the business problems such as “monitoring CO2 emission in logistics for sustainability, solution for anti-money laundering in banking, Data-driven transparency in manufacturing and many cutting-edge consulting solutions with real outcomes.
More information? Please visit https://www.cognizant.com/consulting
About the role
As a Consultant in Artificial Intelligence and Analytics Consulting Nordics, you will contribute in complex projects where you orchestrate the end-to-end capabilities of Cognizant to create a compelling data driven experience. Your management consulting background allows you to work side-by-side with our clients using collaborative methods such as design thinking and agile methodology as well as contributing with your knowledge and expertise in our internal capability teams; advisory, transformation and analytics.
You will play a key role in managing client and account interactions, primarily in your country’s local focus industries. Supported by colleagues and vertical industry experts, you will ensure all-round deliverables in projects and be central in building trust-based relationships for future growth. As a seasoned consultant you will work closely with clients’ onsite to structure their problem, gather data and design solutions . We work across all industries. Specialists from all industries collaborate with our engagement teams to provide deeper insights into the industry.
Typical client problems addressed by Artificial Intelligence and Advisory consulting include:
Define Data/AI strategy, Data and Analytics roadmaps
Data and analytics maturity assessment and roadmaps
Data modernizations Initiatives
Defining data and analytics Operating model
Reports rationalization and reports less world
Define Next Generation Analytics processes
Providing thought leadership on defining the emerging analytics areas
Connects the dots to make data stories on Organization insights
Data Governance Strategy and Implementation roadmaps
Key Responsibilities
Deliver consulting engagements associated with data and analytics projects. Roles will vary widely, but will typically involve elements of business analysis, requirements definition, analytics storytelling, creation of technical and/or business design documents, product management, agile development and facilitation of workshops
Work as part of a team to deliver data & analytics strategy projects, including current state assessments, high level solution design and roadmap development
Support business development activities in the form of gathering best practices for RFI/RFP responses and writing proposals.
Interacts with senior management at a client and/or within Client on matters where they may need to gain acceptance on an alternate approach
Help strengthen client's confidence in Cognizant and Cognizant's ability to deliver.
Support AIA Advisory Community Leaders in the development of AIA Advisory offerings and assets
Participate in continuous learning and development activities in order to maintain ‘leading edge’ skills relevant to our clients
Our ideal candidate
Experience from Stakeholder management or project management
Should be able to demonstrate exceptional requirement techniques with minimal direction from engagement management.
Should have ability to break down high level use case requirements into MVP’s and user stories in the backlog together with Product owner.
Foundational level understanding of data science, AI, ML concepts
Experience in working in Agile/Scrum methodologies is a must.
Advantage
Previous experience with consulting will be an added advantage
Banking and Financial services domain exposure is good to have
Experience in SAFe will be an advantage
Exposure in working in project involving latest technologies like Big Data, Azure Cloud, DevOps, Machine Learning will be good to have.
About Cognizant
Cognizant is one of the world’s leading professional services companies, transforming clients’ business, operating and technology models for the digital era. Our unique industry-based, consultative approach helps clients envision, build and run more innovative and efficient businesses. Headquartered in the U.S., Cognizant, a member of the NASDAQ-100, is ranked 205 on the Fortune 500 and is consistently listed among the most admired companies in the world.

What you can expect
Become part of the ‘flag ship’ success story – We go through enormous growth!
Based in Sweden – we have offices across CE and opportunity to work for Clients across the regions
Organization driven by technology – We have tremendous technology backbone
Open, ‘can do’ team spirit
Environment where you can make your own ideas reality
Drive your own career
Market conform benefits

Employee Status : Full Time Employee
Shift : Day Job
Travel : No
Job Posting : Sep 22 2022
About Cognizant
Cognizant (Nasdaq-100: CTSH) is one of the world's leading professional services companies, transforming clients' business, operating and technology models for the digital era. Our unique industry-based, consultative approach helps clients envision, build and run more innovative and efficient businesses. Headquartered in the U.S., Cognizant is ranked 185 on the Fortune 500 and is consistently listed among the most admired companies in the world. Learn how Cognizant helps clients lead with digital at www.cognizant.com or follow us @Cognizant.

Title: IAM Consultant
Description:
Innofactor upplever stor efterfrågan efter Identity Management och vi genomför just nu några av de största projekten i Norden. Vi söker en ny Identity Consultant till vårt identitetsteam med minst några års erfarenhet inom området Identity Access Management.
Om Innofactor
Innofactor är ett unikt Microsoftfokuserat företag med över 550 anställda i Norden. På Innofactor Sverige får du arbeta med intressanta och utmanande projekt tillsammans med erfarna och engagerade kollegor. Vi hjälper företag och organisationer att öka sin lönsamhet och konkurrenskraft genom att integrera och effektivisera arbetsprocesser och verksamhetssystem.
Vi söker
Dig som vill vara med på en tillväxtresa för att tillsammans bli den ledande leverantören av digital transformation och molnlösningar. Vi ser att vår personal är utåtriktade och ständigt strävar efter att ligga i framkant när det kommer till Microsofts teknologier.
Dig som vill arbeta som konsult i Identity Access teamet, vars uppgift är att leverera moderna lösningar som stödjer och förbättrar kundens verksamhet men även att designa och utveckla lösningar och/eller integrationer med andra system.
Dig som har följande kvalifikationer;
Hands-on erfarenhet av Microsoft Identity Manager
Kännedom om Microsofts Enterprise Mobility + Security
Erfarenhet av Azure AD och gärna kringliggande tjänster som t ex Azure B2C eller AIP
Bekväm med att hålla i workshops inom ditt kunskapsområde
Vilja att ligga i teknikens framkant och att ständigt lära dig nya saker
Positiv och lösningsorienterad
Engagemang att driva området Identitet framåt, vara ett tekniskt flaggskepp och motivator
Vi erbjuder
I Sverige är vi drygt 70 erfarna och engagerade kollegor som arbetar med intressanta och utmanande projekt inom Microsoft Dynamics 365, Office 365, Power Platform, Data & Analytics Platform och Azure. Vi är en Microsoft Gold Partner i 15 kategorier och har fått utmärkelsen Microsoft Dynamics Partner, vilket vi är väldigt stolta över.
En kreativ och dynamisk arbetsplats där vi jobbar tillsammans, hjälper och utmanar varandra och har roligt på vägen. Tillsammans bildar vi ett starkt team för att möta marknadens krav på innovativa och avancerade verksamhetslösningar. Vårt huvudsakliga uppdrag är att ge både organisationer och individer chansen att göra skillnad i den digitala världen. Vi tycker också att det är viktigt att du som anställd får en bra balans mellan arbete och privatliv.
Vi har våra lokaler på Drottninggatan mitt i centrala Stockholm. Det finns även möjligheter att arbeta remote, om man önskar att utgå från sin hemadress. Innofactor är en arbetsplats där vi tror på ett ömsesidigt förtroende, respekt och stöd. Våra anställda står i centrum.
Är du intresserad? Skicka in din ansökan med CV och brev redan idag, så hör vi av oss.
Tillsättning sker löpande.

Title: Experienced technology consultants to our office in Malmö
Description:
We are experiencing a growing demand for our services and are searching for experienced consultants to join our Technology-team in Malmö. You will be part of a skilled and experienced team of consultants working in the intersection between business and technology to help clients make best use of technology to create new business opportunities. We are also helping clients with project management of business-critical IT projects and IT advisory assignments spanning from strategic advisory to client-side management of solution implementations. Our team in Malmö includes about 20 colleagues who are working closely together. We enjoy an entrepreneurial and familiar culture locally while also being part of the greater Sweden practice and collaborating with our other offices in Gothenburg and Stockholm.
In our new colleagues’ profile, we would like to see following requirements:
M Sc Engineering, Economics or other education that is deemed relevant
A proven track record of 2+ (2-6) years in consulting, typically in one or several of the following areas:
IT transformation
Data & Analytics
IT project management
IT strategy/digital strategy
IT procurement
IT governance
IT benchmarking and maturity assessment and improvement
Change management
Agile methodologies
Solution/technical architecture
CRM, eCommerce, campaign management, multi-channel marketing
ERP (finance, SCM, HR/HCM)
Robotics process automation (RPA), artificial intelligence (AI)
Internet of things (IoT)
Experience of delivering in projects
Knowledge in Microsoft Tools to aid day-to-day business activities: Excel, PowerPoint, MS Project etc.
Business mindset, strong analytical skills, team spirit and an ambition to thrive in a challenging and fast-paced environment
Comfortable in an international environment and willing to travel to client assignments abroad
Fluency in both Swedish and English (written and spoken)
What we offer:
A unique opportunity to carry out challenging projects, spanning from strategic advisory to advanced analytics and solution implementation
Exciting career opportunities and possibilities to learn and grow as fast as you desire
Highly competent and down-to-earth colleagues

Benefits of working in both a smaller and bigger company contexts
