Social events and sports activities throughout the year!
If this opportunity sparks your interest, we would be happy to receive your application (CV and cover letter) as soon as possible. Interviews will be held continuously.
About BearingPoint
BearingPoint is an independent management and technology consultancy firm with European roots and a global reach. The company operates in three units: Consulting, Solutions and Ventures. Consulting covers the advisory business; Solutions provides the tools for successful digital transformation, regulatory technology and advanced analytics; Ventures drives the financing and development of start-ups. BearingPoint’s clients include many of the world’s leading companies and organizations. The firm has a global consulting network with more than 10,000 people and supports clients in over 75 countries, engaging with them to achieve measurable and sustainable success.

Title: IT Business Relationship Manager - Pharmaceutical Technology Development
Description:
IT Business Relationship Manager - Pharmaceutical Technology Development
Macclesfield, (UK) Gaithersburg, (USA) Gothenburg, (Sweden)
Do you have expertise in Bio-pharma industry trends, and passion for creating business strategy’s? If so, AstraZeneca might be the one for you!
AstraZeneca is a global, innovation-driven BioPharmaceutical business that focuses on the discovery, development and commercialisation of prescription medicines for some of the globes most serious disease. But we’re more than one of the world’s leading pharmaceutical companies.
At AstraZeneca, we 're dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
ABOUT OUR IT TEAM
The PT&D function is comprised of c.1400 people spread across three major hubs in Macclesfield (UK), Gothenburg (Sweden), Durham (US). This function is accountable for the development of AZ’s small molecule portfolio, sitting in the value chain between R&D and Commercial Manufacturing. The IT Strategies, Services and Solutions that the PT&D IT Capability role is ultimately accountable for span the needs of PT&D’s Laboratories, Pilot Plants and Clinical Trials Supply Chain. It encompasses both the foundational systems of record as well as more transformational digital solutions including AI and Machine Learning.
Here our work has a direct impact on patients – transforming our ability to develop life-changing medicines. We empower the business to operate at its best and lead a new way of working, combining pioneering science with leading digital technology platforms and data. All with a passion to impact lives through data, analytics, AI, machine learning and more. Join us at a crucial stage of our journey in becoming a digital and data-led enterprise. Make the impossible possible by building partnerships and ecosystems, creating new ways of working and driving scale and speed to deliver exponential growth. Focused and committed, and backed with the investment to succeed, we’re driving cross-company change to disrupt the entire industry. There are countless opportunities to learn and grow, whether that’s exploring new technologies in hackathons, or transforming the roles and work of colleagues, forever. Shape your own path, with support all the way. A diverse set of minds that work cross-functionally and inclusively together. Be part of a team that has the backing to innovate, disrupt an industry and change lives.
About the role
The PT&D IT Capability Lead role drives the IT Business Partnership with the global business function of Pharmaceutical Technology & Development (PT&D). The role reports to the Capability Lead for Develop, Make and Digital Transformation within the Operations IT organisation of AstraZeneca’s IT Function, with dotted line reporting to the Senior VP of PT&D with a seat on the PT&D Extended Leadership Team.
This role will lead the identification of innovative technology solutions, to create maximum competitive advantage, prioritising high impact business value outcomes whilst ensuring available technology is fully exploited. Managing a team of IT Business Partners, Project Managers, Scrum Masters and Business Analysts, this role is accountable for the successful delivery of these solutions, orchestrating capabilities drawn from across wider Operations IT and AZ IT Function as a whole.
The PT&D IT Capability Lead will use their IT expertise, bio-pharma industry trends and in-depth understanding of AZ business priorities to lead the functional/capability IT strategy development, investment planning, and delivery. You will develop strategic relationships at the highest levels with the senior Leaders in Pharmaceutical Technology & Development, GPO/BPO owners of the drug development process, and global centre of excellence (e.g., Digital Transformation Leaders), identifying ways for IT to partner achieving and exceeding business objectives. This role will lead the identification of innovative technology solutions, to create maximum competitive advantage, focused on high impact business outcomes and will ensure current technology is fully exploited for business benefit. The role will be accountable for the successful delivery of programs, projects, and products.
Be responsible for the strategic IT relationship with senior Pharmaceutical Technology & Development (PT&D) business leaders and capability areas GPO/BPO’s, developing a deep understanding of the business strategies, priorities and challenges, ensuring that IT investment is aligned to business objectives.
Partner with relevant IT Teams to ensure that all IT services used by the PT&D Function meet the agreed performance outcomes and drive continuous improvement initiatives as required.
Ensure the wider IT strategy is clearly communicated and understood by senior PT&D business leaders
Proactively lead IT demand with the business, negotiating expectations to ensure alignment with IT strategy, architecture and delivery capacity
Gain PT&D business leadership commitment to IT initiatives, using specialist knowledge identify relevance of established or new IT services
Contribute to all aspects of the business/capability areas by using deep Thought Leadership in the Pharmaceutical Development area to influence the strategic direction
Proactively seek opportunities through internal and external networks, for IT to deliver innovative solutions to customer issues/challenges and situations where groundbreaking technological innovations can be deployed.
Lead IT functional/capability governance including steering groups and advisory boards.
Develop and lead the global IT/digital strategy and global solution roadmaps for the PT&D capability business areas.
Drive Ideation, Innovation, and MVPs to continually improve and/or transform the business area.
Own the IT Solutions/Products for the PT&D capability area working with relevant BPOs to drive the feature backlogs and prioritisation.
Ensure the successful outcome from delivery of programs and projects for the PT&D functional area.
Collaborate with PT&D to ensure the development of business cases and ensure robust return on investment and TCO of solutions/products.
Drive the Pharmaceutical Technology & Development capability areas data, analytics, and AI use cases, collaborating with the DAAI team.
Lead the strategic vendor relationships for the capability area owned solutions
Lead and development Ops IT Pharmaceutical Technology & Development function to ensure the delivery of innovation, projects and programs meet the business outcomes. Ensure appropriate use of Dev Ops, Agile and Scrum ways of working.
Essential Skills
Rich experience of bio-pharma industry with knowledge and background in Pharmaceutical Technology & Development
Experience of identification and implementation of innovative technology solutions
Evidence of leading and developing innovative solutions
Experience of defining the business strategies and influencing the vision of senior leaders
Experience of leading high value business cases & mobilising high value investments
Experience in managing, developing and leading virtual teams
A consistent track record of delivering results
Excellent verbal and written communication skills including presenting
Excellent influencing, networking and team working skills
High level awareness of developments in the Information Technology marketplace
Able to manage and lead negotiations, expectations, and solutions across complex partner groups
Expert relationship building skills with the ability to influence others to achieve objectives
Expertise in planning, change management and problem solving and able to resolve issues of a highly complex and strategic nature
Proven ability to relate and respond to business needs in an IT environment
WHY JOIN US?
We’re a network of entrepreneurial self-starters who contribute to something far bigger. There’s a diversity of expertise in our Technology group that’s unique to AstraZeneca – it allows us to dive deep into exploring new innovative technology. We enable AstraZeneca to perform at its peak by delivering world-class technology and data solutions. Our work unlocks the potential of science. We optimise and evolutionise AstraZeneca by maximising efficiencies and finding new ways to drive productivity. From automation to data simplification. We’re not afraid to take ownership and run with it. Empowered with unrivalled freedom. A place to be open and transparent – we speak up, think creatively and share ideas. Our diverse contributions help us to make better decisions. But we have a constant drive to innovate, and an appreciation for high standards. It takes challenging the status quo to add value in our ever-evolving environment. We love it here because put simply, we make a meaningful impact.
Technology at AstraZeneca is a home for purposeful disruptors!
SO, WHAT’S NEXT?
Are you already imagining yourself joining our team? Good, because we’d love to hear from you! Click the link to apply and we’ll be in touch as soon as we can.
WHERE CAN I FIND OUT MORE?
Our Social Media, Follow AstraZeneca on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/1603/
Follow AstraZeneca on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/astrazenecacareers/
Follow AstraZeneca on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/astrazeneca_careers/?hl=en
Competitive salary & benefits on offer.

Title: Bli våran nästa Specialistsäljare inom GCC!
Description:
TD SYNNEX is looking for two Inside Sales Specialist join our Nordic GCC (Global Computing Components) Business Unit. This is a fantastic opportunity to join an exciting, fast-paced industry in a developing, encouraging, and motivational organization with a fantastic culture
Does it sound interesting and are you up for the challenge? Keep reading more and apply!
Locations: Solna, Stockholm -Sweden
Job type: Full time, permanent
Start: According to mutually agreement

The role
GCC works with selling volume consumer and enterprise grade components to various segments and channels, design and build specialized computing and infrastructure solutions. We also work with industry-leading software and hardware vendors that enable our partners to bring validated, specialized and integrated solutions to market quickly and efficiently. The GCC business unit has experienced tremendous growth over the last years, and there is a strong plan in place for continued growth!
As an Inside Sales Specialist in GCC you will have two main focus areas, namely to:
Deliver best in class support to the business development managers in managing and supporting our largest customers ensuring world class service
Be responsible for your own customer portfolio with the ambition to acquire new customers and drive growth and positive development with smaller customers

This is a diverse role where you will be able to put a lot of skills to work and you will have a great opportunity develop as a person. As such you will be experiencing a role that consists of many different tasks within sales, planning, forecasting, purchasing, go to market execution as well as operational tasks such article and bid management. In addition to be an integral part of the Nordics team you will also be working close with our European team in driving and optimizing the business.

About you
You are a skilled salesperson who is good at creating relationships with both customers and vendors, you have a commercial mindset as well as flair/interest for IT. You get motivated by generating results and delivering excellent customer service, and you respond quickly and professionally to customer inquiries. You are outgoing and energetic and at the same time have an eye for detail - even in situations where things are going fast.
It’s important that you can work independently and at the same time you are also a team player. You have a winning attitude, you thrive when being a part of a team where the pace is high, the energy and humor is fantastic and where we help each other!
If you feel this could be something for you then send us a short summary and your CV.

What we offer
A truly exciting role with plenty of room to grow, the chance to make your mark on our business, work with some of the most motivated and brightest people in the industry. We offer a competitive compensation package that matches your skills and experience.
TD SYNNEX is a fantastic place to work, and we embrace values such an inclusion, integrity and collaboration, trust, and you should be able to identify

We also offer:
30 vacation days/year
Flexible remote work, 2-3 days per week
Health care allowance 4 000 kr/year (friskvårdsbidrag)
Extended parental pay (according to collective agreement)
ITP 1 - Employment pension (according to collective agreement)
Stylish, modern and fresh office near Westfield/Mall of Scandinavia
Discounts for the gyms Nordic Wellness, SATS and Fitness 24/7 (NW in the building)

Contact person
If you have any questions about the job, please feel free to contact rekrytering@tdsynnex.com

Application
We conduct interviews continuously and our ambition is to have the right candidate in place as soon as possible.
There is no need to write up a long-motivated application just submit a short resume about yourself and your resume/CV.

About TD SYNNEX
TD SYNNEX is a leading global distributor and solutions aggregator for the IT ecosystem.
TD SYNNEX is ranked No. 60 on the Fortune 500® and has been named one of Fortune’s World’s Most Admired Companies for nine straight years
We’re an innovative partner helping more than 150,000 customers in 100+ countries to maximize the value of technology investments, demonstrate business outcomes and unlock growth opportunities. TD SYNNEX has approximately 23,500 co-workers worldwide who are dedicated to uniting compelling IT products, services and solutions from 1,500+ best-in-class technology vendors.
Our edge-to-cloud portfolio is anchored in some of the highest-growth technology segments including cloud, cybersecurity, big data/analytics, IoT, mobility and everything as a service.
TD SYNNEX is committed to serving customers and communities, and we believe we can have a positive impact on our people and our planet, intentionally acting as a respected corporate citizen. We aspire to be a diverse and inclusive employer of choice for talent across the IT ecosystem.
For more information, visit www.TDSYNNEX.com follow us on Twitter, LinkedIn, Facebook and Instagram.

Title: Business Analyst
Description:
The company
Our client requires a Business Analyst to join their fast-growing team and develop business requirements from the ground up with their customers and translate these into technical requirements. Their customers are primarily Telecoms biased, however, not exclusively and an understanding of large scale IT systems is ideal.
Theyare a dynamic and exciting company that started up 5 years ago. Theyhave some of the largest names in Telecoms as their clients and theycontinue to innovate with their products - not only to keep them ahead of their competition but to create industry best and technology direction, as well as thought leadership.
Theyspecialise and are a leader in ETL, Big Data, Analytics, and Machine Learning, with award-winning solutions that transform their clients' operations.
The company continues to grow, and this role represents an excellent opportunity to join a successful and ambitious team that strives to over achieve.

Ideally you should have between 3-6 years relevant experience in telecoms, Network / Radio experience is good but not vital. You must be able to demonstrate experience in gathering, developing and rationalising requirements and then producing detailed requirement specifications and process flows for software developers.
Experience in the following is ideal:
Knowledge of CRM / Business Intelligence.
Billing system.
Configuration Management system experience.
Provisioning systems.
Performance management systems.
Development & execution of test specifications.
System installation and end to end delivery
Requirements gathering and analysis
Analysing and building advanced SQL queries for use cases such as extracts, KPIs etc
Developing and maintaining requirements and design documentation
Additional Experience (preferably in Telecoms):
Mobile Telecoms Networks.
3GPP standards.
Radio Data migration.
Desired Technical Skills:
UNIX Operating System experience and related script creation and maintenance.
Understanding of Hadoop, and related tools (Yarn, ZooKepper, etc).
Understanding of Analytical Tools, such as MapReduce / Spark.
Use of SQL and other SQL type tools with NoSQL database tools (e.g. MongoDB)
Familiarity with Python, Java
Use of visualisation tools such as Kibana, Tableau, etc
Familiarity with Cache Technologies, such as Redis.
Familiarity with Virtualisation and Container Methods.
Familiarity with Alarm Generation and Monitoring Approaches
Essential skills:
Excellent written and verbal communication.
Problem solving.
Flexibility.
Well organised and self-motivated.
Willingness and flexibility with travelling.
You will need to:
Spend time with customers in the UK and abroad, and will have to lead them through the requirement gathering and implementation processes.
Arrange meetings and interviews to gather the requirements and verify them with the customer.
Turn business requirements into meaningful technical requirements for software developers to build from.
Track progress of development and check direction.
Develop test specifications and test plans.
Assist with on-site implementations.
Educated to degree level (or equivalent) in a technical subject.
This is a central client-facing role, requiring an ability to guide the customer through the complex process of billing systems change, and rewarding you with the satisfaction of providing clients with a first-class service.
All candidates must be able to travel abroad at short notice, once international travel restrictions have eased sufficiently.
**Please ignore the salary stated in the job board, as it will be negotiated depending on the candidate's skillset and experience

Title: Senior Finance Analyst - Nordics
Description:
General information
All posting locations: Stockholm, , Sweden
Job Function: 03 - Finance
Date Published: 25-Jan-2023
Ref #: R-54736
Description & Requirements

About Kraft Heinz Nordics

Kraft Heinz has recently changed its geographical footprint- making Nordics a top priority within the newly formed Northern Europe business unit together with UK & Ireland. With this comes very bold growth plans for the Nordic region- with increased investments behind our customers and consumers. To deliver on this- Kraft Heinz has established an exceptional team of talents from different backgrounds and with different skills. Our ambition is to build on a strong base while also entering new categories- to create additional value for our consumers and customers and establish Kraft Heinz as a leading food company within the Nordics.
About the Position
We have an excellent opportunity available for an experienced Finance professional to make a difference at Kraft Heinz. The Senior Finance Analyst role lies within the Northern Europe Business Unit (UK- Ireland- and Nordics) with Nordics area of responsibility. You’ll be working in a high performing team- alongside peers always trying to reach the next level. You’ll be reporting into Head of Finance and Revenue management. Get ready for a lot of collaboration with sales team and clients. Gate keeping our trade investments and helping to build strong RGM plans will be your primary responsibilities.

Main Responsibilities
Role split 70% Trade investment / 30% RGM
Providing support and supervision of our invoice to cash cycle:
ensuring correct pricing and needed accruals are in place
guiding disputes team and being on the front line of communication with clients for finance specific matters
working with receivables and overdue- providing support to dedicated team to timely resolve all the matters with cash collection
Gate keeping promo and contract terms planning: approvals and proof of performance
Reconciling trade investments related balance sheet general ledgers
Being a key user of promo planning tool and order to cash system- providing support to sales team
Leading key RGM projects and routines with focus on increasing profitability and Promo ROI analysis- providing recommendations to sales teams
Monitor- check- and highlight key performance indicators to relevant internal stakeholders and influence decision-making to ensure delivery of business target
Delivering continuous improvement in the quality of analysis- output- and visibility provided to the Nordics leadership team
Your Qualification
Education: minimum bachelor’s degree
Work Experience: Preferable to have at least 3 years’ experience of finance analytics- understanding of financial reports (P&L focus- managerial accounts)
Knowledge: P&L understanding- Advanced Excel knowledge- Basic accounting- experience working with SAP a plus- experience working with Nielsen a plus- desire to continue building skillset in data analytics (Tableau- Alteryx)
Language: Fluency in English is needed
Professional Attributes
Analytical and structured
We’re a very data driven company. You know how to translate complex data into a simple solution with your analytical mindset
Attention to details and structured approach is a very key for this role
Ability to Simplify
We like to keep it simple. And to execute fast. Your ability to simplify will be highly appreciated- when you provide simple solutions dealing with complex challenges
Project management skills
Time management has no secrets for you. You’re organized- structured- and always have an overview of all the deliverables. You know how to bring multiple projects to a successful ending within the given timeframe
High pressure
You don’t get easily stressed by pressure- on the opposite- a demanding and dynamic environment is what keeps you energized
Team player
Achieving results is nice but achieving results with the team is simply the best. You’re a team player- which means you’re sometimes a leader- sometimes a follower but always working towards the same common goal together with your teammates
What we offer you
Atmosphere and flexibility of a small team with global company capabilities and knowledge
Great cross functional learning opportunities
A competitive salary and excellent bonus structure (above market)
Permanent contract: we believe in doing big bets on people
A unique chance to make an impact from the start
Working with and caring for some of the strongest food brands in the world.
A people-oriented organization who wants the best for you.
Training and support to boost your growth opportunities.
An environment with passionate employees working to provide the best possible results for our business.
Great office perks at our Nordic HQ in central Stockholm.
If this sounds like something for you- do not hesitate to apply now. Applications will be reviewed continuously- and we would not want you to miss out!
About Us
The Kraft Heinz Company is one of the largest food and beverage companies in the world, with eight $1 billion+ brands and global sales of approximately $25 billion. We’re a globally trusted producer of high-quality, great-tasting, and nutritious foods for over 150 years. Our brands are truly global, with products produced and marketed in over 40 countries. These beloved products include condiments and sauces, cheese and dairy, meals, meats, refreshment beverages, coffee, infant and nutrition products, and numerous other grocery products in a portfolio of more than 200 legacy and emerging brands.
No matter the brand, we’re united under one vision: To sustainably grow by delighting more consumers globally. Bringing this vision to life is our team of 39,000+ food lovers, creative thinkers, and high performers worldwide. Together, we help provide meals to those in need through our global partnership with Rise Against Hunger. We also stand committed to responsible, sustainable practices that extend to every facet of our business, our consumers, and our communities. Every day, we’re transforming the food industry with bold thinking and unprecedented results. If you share our passion – and are ready to create the future, build a legacy, and lead as a global citizen – there’s only one thing to do: join our table and let’s make life delicious!
Our Culture of Ownership, Meritocracy and Collaboration
We're not afraid to think differently. Embrace new ideas. Dream big. We empower our people at every level – from entry-level intern to senior leader – to own their work. We share a responsibility to think like Owners – to be mindful of the collective and sustained success of Kraft Heinz – which we apply to every situation, every day.
As part of Kraft Heinz, you're supported to grow and achieve. You’re expected to bring your authentic self to work every day, to lead with humility, and drive outstanding performance at every level – and you’ll be rewarded. You’re given opportunities to leave a mark and build a legacy. But you won’t do it alone. You’re supported by passionate teammates along the way, and our collective, collaborative spirit fuels our incredible progress.
Kraft Heinz is an Equal Opportunity Employer - Underrepresented Ethnic Minority Groups/Women/Veterans/Individuals with Disabilities/Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity and other protected classes.

Title: Senior Cloud Engineer
Description:
Why Nasdaq
When you work at Nasdaq, you’re working for more open and transparent markets so that more people can access opportunities. Connections can be made, jobs can be created, and communities can thrive. We want all our employees to have access to opportunities, too. That means planning for career growth, ensuring you have the tools you need, and promoting an inclusive culture where we’re all valued for our unique perspectives.
Here, you will work for a global tech leader committed to breaking down barriers to inclusive prosperity. We see technology as a means to free people up to work together more productively and effectively by centralizing data, analytics, and market intelligence.
Here, we’re committed to building a more diverse and inclusive workforce. Not only is it our responsibility to do better, but we also need representative voices to power the fresh thinking that is vital for our business and our clients.
What we offer
As a part of Nasdaq's Enterprise Architecture group, the Cloud Platform Engineering team oversees the common patterns and practices used by application development and operations teams across Nasdaq to build cloud infrastructure. As our new member, you will work with a group of enthusiastic and like-minded cloud experts. Together with your team, you will be responsible for maintaining and improving the Cloud Automation Pipeline, as well as helping other Nasdaq teams understand how to build and operate their products in the cloud.
You can expect an autonomous but fast-paced work environment where you are recognized for your results and ability to drive things forward. Every day brings many opportunities to learn & grow and rewards with the global impact we create.
What you will do
As a Cloud Platform Engineer, you will be responsible for the design, development, testing, and operation of the infrastructure supporting the company’s solutions, as well as the development process by which that infrastructure is engineered. Besides working closely with your colleagues in Bangalore, you will also work closely with teammates globally and across all of Nasdaq.
Expect responsibilities like :
Develop infrastructure per Nasdaq standards and practices.
Work with architects to collect requirements and design solutions for new projects.
Advise and mentor engineers across teams, promoting Nasdaq tools, technologies, patterns, and practices.
Craft and maintain team knowledgebase articles and FAQs.
Provide support for Nasdaq engineering and operations teams.
Maintain infrastructure, repair bugs, and respond to downtime when needed.
What We Expect From You
Demonstrate expert proficiency using cloud engineering tools and technologies (terraform, Kubernetes, etc)
Demonstrate expert knowledge of software development patterns and practices
Have prior experience training and mentoring junior Cloud Engineers
Have prior experience coordinating team efforts to complete projects
Demonstrate proficiency in building and deploying applications using both high-level programming languages (C#, Java, etc) and common scripting languages (PowerShell, Python, etc)
Have 6 to 9 years of proven experience working as a cloud engineer or similar roles
What Would Be Helpful To Succeed in the Role
Demonstrate expert knowledge of infrastructure-as-code patterns and toolsets
Have prior experience building centralized infrastructure platforms
Have experience across many different cloud service providers
About Nasdaq Umeå
Nasdaq is expanding its Nordic tech hub in Umeå with the office located in the city center, next to Utopia mall. Our office is close to gyms, restaurants, and public transport. Nasdaq Sweden also provides its employees with 32 annual vacation days and additional flex days. We offer a competitive salary package that includes annual bonus and equity plans as well as an employee stock purchase program.
The recruitment process is ongoing so please submit your application in English at your earliest convenience.
Come as You Are
Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

Title: Senior Software Developer
Description:
Elsa is growing and we are looking for empathic senior software developers (full-time employees or long-term freelancers) with different interests and skillsets to enrich our warm and passionate team on the journey of supporting people with a chronic disease to live life to its fullest.

Who we are and what we believe
Elsa was founded to change the fact that there is no science-based, individualised treatment support for people living with chronic disease to optimise their quality of life.
Our goal is to be a motivational and educational digital platform that brings individuals, families, health care providers, medical companies and scientists together through seamless data sharing and powerful communication for a greater good: to detect and manage the illness, improve healthcare and empower the individual to reach a new normal and live life to its fullest.

What you'll do
As a Senior Software Developer, you will be a part of our 15 people (and growing) product team and contribute to improving the Elsa app and the systems around it.

On a day-to-day basis, you will:
develop mobile apps, websites, backend services and/or data pipelines
collaborate and discuss product, design and UX
contribute your skills, experience and creativity to form (and, when needed, question) strategic discussions, team building activities and innovative work

Who you are

You probably have (most of the following):
a calling to impact people's lives for the better
experience with JavaScript/TypeScript or Python, or enough software development experience to pick up a new language fast
solid experience with K8s, React or React Native
worked at a startup or used agile development processes
willingness to coach, mentor and empower your team members
It is great if you have (any of the following):
scaled a popular app in terms of number of users, but also faster iteration and experimentation
used Pandas or Jupyter
built data analytics stacks using ELT
developed medical devices, SaMD or worked in regulated domains
worked with or are really interested in data privacy or system/information security
You need to be:
fluent in English
a team-player who thrives in dynamic working environment and a growing team
Keywords:
TypeScript, react-native, CK8s, dbt, growth.

How we work
At Elsa Science we strive to make an impact on the world and to improve people’s lives. In order to do so, we place importance on our individual mental and physical health, which includes both caring about each other and our users. Our users are also at the center of everything that we do and we are co-creating Elsa in dialog with them and our other collaborators.
As the second part our name might reveal, we love science and facts! We get just as excited about what’s already been discovered about health and lifestyle habits as we do about all the opportunities yet to be discovered. Exploring is by nature uncertain and unpredictable, as well as exciting and fun, and that's also the nature of being part of Elsa!

I have had jobs in the past where the end result does not feel really meaningful. But I want to do something that serves a purpose, that actually improves someone’s life and creates value beyond my technical bubble. As a result, my life improves knowing that I help others. - Johan, developer


All my colleagues really care about each other and it has a spillover effect on how we approach and treat our users. It feels really refreshing. - Monique, developer

What we offer
Employee stock ownership plan and occupational pension (ITP1)
The opportunity to dedicate two hours to physical activity on Monday mornings, we call it Hjärnstark or Brain Monday!
36h work week (we have Friday afternoons free)
30 days of vacation year one and 35 days the second year and onwards
A yearly wellness allowance (friskvårdsbidrag) of 3000 SEK
Your mobile phone bill is covered up to 1 000 SEK per month, incl cost of upgrading to a new phone
Wonderful office in central Stockholm, with a possibility to work remotely
(We also have favourable alternatives for freelancers.)

Title: Digital Marketing & Sales (Intern)
Description:
Who we are
We are an early-stage startup hell-bent on improving the post-purchase experience in the e-commerce industry, starting with the biggest pain point: returns. We move fast and expect a lot because we're working on something that will truly make the e-commerce industry more sustainable, financially and environmentally. With COVID19 crisis accelerating the migration from offline to online, together with booming acquisition costs, increasing customer loyalty has become paramount. At the same time, with increasing online sales, retailers suffer from booming returns.
yayloh is a SaaS solution for e-commerce retailers, which digitalizes and automates the return process and unleashes the potential of return data. yayloh will increase customer satisfaction and loyalty while improving retailers profitability and reducing environmental impact. Using data analytics and applied machine learning, yayloh allows e-commerce retailers to understand their customers needs on an advanced level. yayloh is backed by the early-stage VC Antler. Also worth mentioning, we have happy customers and a growing pipeline in different countries!
What we’re looking for
We are looking for an intern to work hand in hand with the CEO in the coming months, which will be crucial for the development of the start-up.
We need a problem solver, someone that see opportunities and potential to improve. You will play an important role in taking yayloh to the next level - thus, you should desire to go above and beyond to deliver and grow as an individual.
Tasks:
Growth hacking/sales: develop the pipeline of potential customers, online retail market screening, preparation of introduction emails, production of PowerPoint presentations for meetings, update of the CRM follow-up
Digital marketing: prepare, launch and monitor online campaigns (LinkedIn, Instagram), product content for inbound marketing (blog post, reports)
This internship will be a great opportunity to experience what it is to work in an early-stage start-up environment.
The intern mission and tasks will depend on the intern competencies and aspirations to grow and this is a great chance to have a steep learning curve.
Requirements
Must-have: excellent written English communication skills
Ideally, previous digital marketing internship experience in a fast-pace environment or start-ups
What we offer?
Being part of a very early stage start-up where we expect you to be independent, creative, free thinking. We are two co-founders with a strong skillset combination, with respective deep experience in retail and software development.
The dream team
We are international from day-one with a co-founding team from France and India and English is the company language so everyone feels included. Our first market is the Nordics but we dream big and are building a global company.
We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters so we don’t see failures but learning opportunities. Innovation is at the heart of everything we do and we believe anything is possible when you can think freely, without boundaries nor pre-set frameworks.
We don’t count your hours and you can work from your couch if this is where you perform the best, what we will care about is how much you contribute to make the product better!
How to apply?
Send Resume and short intro email to sophie@yayloh.com

Title: Senior Business Intelligence/Data Specialist till Columbus
Description:
Om ditt hjärta slår snabbare när du hör SQL och BI nämnas i samma mening och du vill hugga direkt in i diskussionen när det diskuteras BI-lösningar på lördagsmiddagen? Då tror vi att du skulle trivas hos oss!

Om rollen
Som Senior BI-konsult hos oss är du delaktig i hela processen - från initial dialog med kunden, framtagning av kravspecifikationer och design, till implementering. Du identifierar nya affärsmöjligheter för våra kunder genom att omvandla data till värderfulla insikter. Tidsmässigt löper projekten i ett fåtal dagar vid mindre delprojekt till flera månader eller löpande hos våra långsiktiga kundsamarbeten. Du arbetar parallellt med flera kundprojekt och ingår i kundteam tillsammans med teamets BI-konsulter, arkitekter och våra konsulter från affärsområdena för Dynamics, M3, and Digital Commerce. På kundsidan arbetar du nära olika kravställare, process- och systemägare.
Teamet för Data & Analytics har en väl utvecklad arbetsmetod och arbetar aktivt för att lyfta fram nya tankesätt och idéer som gäller oavsett om du är arkitekt eller trainee, bäst idé vinner helt enkelt! Du arbetar hos kund, på något av våra kontor i Malmö, Stockholm, Göteborg eller på distans - på det sätt som du trivs bäst med! Oavsett arbetar du med vår konsultchef Kim Rasmussen.

"På Columbus arbetar jag med många olika områden inom Data & Analytics, allt ifrån uppsättning av datalager, visualiseringar i diverse olika front end-verktyg till att kika på hur vi kan använda ML och AI för att ge mervärde åt våra kunder. Själva processen med att utforma en lösning tillsammans med kund och att få använda den senaste tekniken är väldigt utvecklande!" - Anton, Senior BI-konsult.
Varför Columbus?
Vi har i över 30 år levererat digitala lösningar till våra kunder och det har vi gjort framgångsrikt. Hur kommer det sig? Jo! På Columbus har vi en omfattande branschkunskap som kombineras med ett stort utbud av digitala lösningar och en rejäl dos kundförståelse. Våra olika affärsområden kan dra nytta av varandra och arbeta med samma kunder i olika skeden av sin digitalisering och därmed erbjuda olika spetskompetenser. Vi hjälper våra kunder att forma lösningar efter branschspecifika behov så att de kan nå sin fulla digitala potential.
På Data & Analytics får du vara delaktig i ett område som är strategiskt viktigt för Columbus. Vi är en grupp på 50 konsulter i Skandinavien och vi växer! Columbus är ledande inom Dynamics 365, M3 samt E-Commerce vilket ger oss ett stort internationellt kontaktnät av konsulter. Våra kunder och vår spetskompetens ligger inom tillverkande industri, food & beverage och fashion. Vi tror på att utveckla oss själva och därigenom våra kunder genom att använda oss av den senaste tekniken, som du såklart kommer kunna hålla dig uppdaterad inom.

"På Columbus finns en stor kundflora – vilket ger en bred och intressant inblick i olika typer av projekt och kunder från olika branscher. Det som skiljer oss från andra bolag, utöver att vi också har en egen ERP-leverans, är att vi levererar projekt och inte resurskonsulter. Det finns möjlighet att påverka och förändra både i projekten och i teamet." - Paul, Lösningsarkitekt.
Vad du har med dig
Erfarenhet av flertal BI-projekt där du har levererat goda resultat
Goda kunskaper i T-SQL, Kimball/Inmon Dimensionsmodellering
Tidigare erfarenheter av att inhämta kravställning hos kund, dokumentation och kundrelaterade uppgifter som workshops
Oavsett hur länge du har varit i branschen värdesätter vi att du är nyfiken, har god samarbetsförmåga, tar ägandeskap i ditt arbete, driver projekt och hanterar kundidalog galant! Kommunikation går som en röd tråd i den här rollen och därför behöver du vara flytande i svenska och engelska. Ett intresse för att effektivisera och digitalisera verksamheter är något både vi och våra kunder uppskattar och vi vill gärna höra om spännande erfarenheter du har med dig!
Sitter du dessutom med Python, Machine Learning, Azure Synapse, Databricks och kunskap inom särskilda processvertikaler i bakfickan så slårt det extra högt.
Kan du inte bocka av alla krav? Sök ändå! Vi är alltid intresserade av att knyta kontakt med duktiga BI-konsulter.
Mer om oss
Columbus är ett värdestyrt bolag med engagerade medarbetare som stöttar varandra i både framgång som motgång. Att ha en god balans mellan arbete och fritid är en självklarhet. Vi lämnar utrymme för återhämtning och ser till att arbeta proaktivt med blicken på horisonten. Dessutom så är vi riktigt bra på att fira framgångar och det är inte ovanligt med fika, lyxfrukost och AW på kontoret .
På Columbus har vi trevliga förmåner som ett generöst friskvårdsbidrag, föräldralön, privat pensionsförsäkring och extra ersättning vid sjukdom för att stötta våra medarbetare i livets olika stadier.

Spana in vårt Insta-flöde för att få en bild av hur det är att jobba hos oss genom våra kollegor. Klicka på bilden för att komma till Instagram-kontot.

Helt ofiltrerat har vi samlat in omdömen från nuvarande och tidigare kollegor. Klicka nedan för att läsa mer.

Title: Software Engineer
Description:
Om Hackberry

Hackberry är ett IT-konsultbolag som bygger mobilappar primärt, men vi jobbar även mycket mot backendsystem, UX-design & Data Analytics. Vi växer just nu mer än någonsin och just nu är vi 22 personer på kontoret! Hackberry är ett ganska ungt företag och vi bygger företaget från grunden, vilket ger oss en fantastisk möjlighet att skapa ett innovativt företag som passar den moderna konsulten redan från början. Vi vill expandera med människor som är glada över att bygga Hackberry tillsammans med oss. Vårt nya hem är The Factory, som ligger i ett växande område i Sollentuna. Här arbetar vi under samma tak som en mängd spännande startups och scaleups.

Vi bygger primärt appar för våra kunder! Internt eller på plats hos kund, stora projekt och små, i team eller individuellt, stora etablerade företag eller nya startups. Allt går och allt gör vi. Vi är ett fullservice företag, och kan hantera alla delar av kedjan från idé till koncept, design, UX/UI, utveckling, integration, test, data analytics, support och förvaltning.
Om rollen
Som Software Engineer här på Hackberry kommer du som konsult att få jobba i många spännande projekt hos olika kunder i varierande storlekar. Dina dagar ser olika ut beroende på vilken kund du är på, men en dag här är inte en annan dag lik. Varje dag ställs du inför nya komplexa, men spännande problem att lösa.
Din vardag kommer troligtvis innehålla någon av flertalet arbetsuppgifter: Scrum-genomgång, vidareutveckling av koden, lägga till nya features, jobba tillsammans i stimulerande team (både inhouse på vårt kontor & hos kunden), ha kompetenta kollegor att bolla olika lösningar med, ta en fika eller spela en pingsmatch.
Vem vi tror att du är

Vi söker dig som är tidigare arbetat med systemutveckling. Eftersom vi jobbar som konsulter så är det viktigt att du är flexibel & mångsidig, och att du kan ta dig an nya projekt och miljöer på ett snabbt sätt. Det är även av stor vikt att du kan hantera kunder på ett bra sätt. Vidare har du lätt för att samarbeta med andra människor, är noggrann i din kodning och är kreativ i ditt problemlösning sätt.
Vi förväntar oss att du:
har minst 4 års arbetslivserfarenhet av systemutveckling
har tidigare erfarenheter av cloud-tjänster, gärna AWS eller GCP
har tidigare erfarenheter av att bygga API:er, gärna i Springboot eller node.js, alternativt Django eller liknande
har tidigare erfarenhet av AWS Cloudwatch, Sentry, CrashLytics eller liknande
har mycket goda kunskaper i SQL och noSQL
har mycket goda kunskaper av versionshantering
talar & skriver obehindrat på svenska & engelska
ser positivit på att vårt kontor ligger i Häggvik, Sollentuna.


Vi anser det vara meriterande om du:
har tidigare erfarenheter av Cloud-functions eller AWS Lambda
har tidigare erfarenheter av Firebase
har tidigare erfarenheter av Swagger
har tidigare erfarenheter av GraphQL
har tidigare erfarenheter av Kubernetes
har kännedom kring best practices inom security & OWASP top 10.
Som person är du:
Flexibel
Kreativ
Ansvarstagande
Har en bra samarbetsförmåga
Har en bra problemlösningsförmåga
Har vi fångat ditt intresse?
Skicka in en ansökan redan idag! Urval & intervjuer sker löpande.

Avdelning
Development
Roll
Software Engineer
Platser
Sollentuna - The Factory
Distansarbete
Hybridarbete

KONTAKT
Alexandra Engman
Head of HR – HR

Title: Data Scientist inom Asset Management till Strukton
Description:
Strukton Rail är en av Sveriges ledande privata järnvägsentreprenörer. Idag befinner de sig i ett spännande och expansivt skede och söker därför en Data Scientist inom Asset Management. Asset Management är en del av affärsområde Underhåll, och ansvarar för systemutveckling, integration, dataanalys och rapportering samt verksamhetsutveckling generellt.

Som anställd på Strukton Rail får du möjligheten att anamma en utvecklande roll där du kommer att få vara med i ett företag där arbetet utförs med hjärtat. Du kommer att få vara med och rådgiva beslutsfattare och få möjligheten till utbildningar då personalens utveckling och välmående är A och O för företaget. De tillämpar hybrid arbetsplats, med möjlighet att arbeta hemifrån. Resor inom Sverige kan förekomma.

Plats: Stockholm/Västberga, Västerås, Göteborg, Norrköping, Malmö eller enligt önskemål. Gärna nära Strukton Rails etableringar.
Sista ansökningsdag: 2023-01-29
Utvecklas i din karriär
Bra anställningsförmåner
Varierande arbetsuppgifter
Dina arbetsuppgifter
I rollen som Data Scientist kommer du att ingå i ett team som består av två underhållsingenjörer och tre verksamhetsutvecklare. Tjänsten innebär datamodellering och strukturering samt i viss mån programmering, för att möjliggöra bättre datadriven beslutstagning i stor omfattning.

Du kommer att få chansen att ta företagets förmåga till dataanalys och datadrivet beslutsstöd till nästa nivå för att bättre kunna visualisera infrastrukturens tillstånd och behov av åtgärder till era kunder. Dina huvudsakliga arbetsuppgifter kommer att bestå av att förstå verksamhetens behov och bistå med beslutsstöd. Du kommer att transformera och städa upp data så att den är användbar samt skapa analysmodeller. Du kommer även att tillämpa modeller inom Machine Learning och visualisera data och agera rådgivare mot beslutsfattare.
Din profil och kvalifikationer
För att trivas i rollen som Data Scientist ser vi att du både är analytisk och gillar att agera expert inom ditt område. För att trivas och utvecklas i den entreprenörskultur som präglar Strukton Rails organisation behöver du ha ett strukturerat och kvalitetsmedvetet arbetssätt. Du är självgående och ansvarstagande i ditt arbete och har lätt för att samarbeta. Vi ser gärna att du också är nyfiken och tar initiativ då tjänsten innefattar vidareutveckling av dataanalys.

Krav:
Eftergymnasial utbildning inom relevant område t.ex. systemvetenskap, datateknik, informationsteknologi, business intelligence.
Minst två års arbetslivserfarenhet inom området Data Scientist / Business Intelligence
Erfarenhet av programmering t.ex. Python, R, Java, SQL
Erfarenhet av PowerBI, SAS eller ett liknande data analytics tool.
Erfarenhet av Database management och data vizualisation
Flytande svenska och engelska i tal och skrift
Om kunden
Strukton Rail är en av Sveriges ledande privata järnvägsentreprenörer. De levererar infrastrukturlösningar för järnväg i Skandinavien genom att bygga och underhålla spårsystem. Idag har Strukton Rail cirka 1000 medarbetare och är verksamma i Sverige och våra skandinaviska grannländer. Som en av Sveriges största järnvägsentreprenörer levererar de alltid hållbara och kostnadseffektiva lösningar av hög kvalité.

Du blir delaktig i ett företag där de inte bara arbetar på spår utan även med RÄLS: Respekt, Ärlighet, Lita på, Säkerhet; Strukton Rails värdegrund som de eftersträvar i allt de tar sig an.

Title: Back End Developer
Description:
Who are we?
Stockfiller is a Food tech startup building a new and smarter infrastructure for the food industry. By connecting buyers, suppliers and other partners in our eB2B ecosystem we create value for suppliers, grocery chains, independently owned outlets, wholesalers and transportation companies. Our mission is to:
Eliminate non-value adding costs for all parties
Enable suppliers (from local producers to large multinationals) to sell in hard-to-access channels while helping them improve their performance (outlet visibility, data analytics) and at the same time significantly reducing food waste at the point in the value chain where it truly makes a difference!
Enable retailers to effectively control their spend and save time, while giving them access to a wide range of value adding services to improve their revenue, costs and operations
At Stockfiller you will be given a unique opportunity to gain insight and be a part of a fast-paced, fun scale-up environment in a company with phenomenal growth and reach on primarily the Swedish market, but also other European markets. You will get to work together with awesome business developers, passionate developers and amazing clients. On top of this you will get to work with a great team in a dynamic and inclusive environment with fantastic coffee and fun after works – right in the center of Stockholm!
Our proprietary systems are used by thousands of suppliers, stores and restaurants throughout Europe and this is where You come into the picture – adding even more clients! The position is full-time and based in Stockholm.
About the position:
You will be part of our internal tech team and collaborate closely with our backend Lead to develop and improve our applications, used by thousands of suppliers, stores and restaurants across Europe. Day to day you will work with a modern micro-service based architecture to turn complex business requirement into functionality, but you will also take part in and influence major tech decisions. Since the team is small, you will have the opportunity to have a large impact on technology choices, the tech stack and similar. The position is full time and based in Stockholm.
Who are you?
We believe you have worked at least 2+ years building scalable backend systems, preferably using PHP, Docker, and MongoDB
You are passionate about backend development and technologies in general
You have experience writing performant, secure, scalable, and testable code
You have a genuine interest in new perspective and ideas, and to solve the big problems in life
You are comfortable working both independently as well as together in a team

Title: Postdoc fellowship in AI Image Processing
Description:
Welcome to Linnaeus University! We meet the societal challenges of today and tomorrow in a spirit of openness, curiosity and creativity. By creating arenas for exchange of knowledge from different subjects, fields and cultures, we open up for new ideas and create new opportunities for long-term sustainable societal development. Linnaeus University – where people grow.
Linnaeus University is running various national and European projects that focus on both fundamental and applied research. The Linnaeus University Centre for Data Intensive Sciences and Applications – DISA (www.lnu.se/en/disa) addresses data-driven methods to gain deeper knowledge and understanding in a variety of applications in engineering, science, and humanities. Linnaeus University runs a graduate school for industrial doctoral students that focuses on applied research, addressing the big data and artificial intelligence challenges of our industry partners.
The advertised position will be placed at the department of Computer Science and Media Technology in the research group Data Intensive Software Technologies and Applications –DISTA (https://lnu.se/en//dista/) that studies data-driven approaches, such as machine learning, artificial intelligence, and big data, to automate and improve software development stages. DISTA is a core research area within DISA.
Field of subject for the position: Computer Science with specialization in AI Image Processing
Placement: Department of Computer Science and Media Technology, Faculty of Technology – Växjö Campus, Sweden
Employment: 100% employment full-time for two years with possibility for 1-year extension. At most 20% time can be dedicated to teaching and other departmental tasks.
Start date: According to agreement.
Job description and duties:
The postdoc fellow will focus on the application of deep learning (both supervised and unsupervised approaches) to address complex computer vision and image generation problems. In particular, the goal is to generate and analyze images and videos to address complex problems in different thematic areas, such as forestry, physics, engineering, e-health and software engineering. The postdoc fellow will conduct research within the fields of AI Image Processing in close collaboration with other research groups as well as domain experts within DISA.
In addition, the postdoc fellow will be working with applied research in Deep Learning, Image Generation, and Computer Vision, together with small and medium-sized companies in the region Kalmar and Växjö.
The postdoc fellow is expected to regularly present intermediate/final research results at international conferences and workshops, and publish them in conference proceedings and journals.
Eligibility Requirements
Eligible to be employed are those who have completed a doctoral degree in Computer Science or an equivalent degree. The doctorate shall have been obtained no longer than three years before the expiration date of the application.
Eligibility for this position also requires that the doctoral thesis has a focus on Deep Machine Learning applied to Computer Vision and/or Image Generation used in one or more application areas.
Excellent written and oral communication skills in English are required.
Assessment criteria:
Excellent knowledge in the applied research areas of Deep Machine Learning and Computer Vision/Image Generation is a must. Good programming skills in relevant languages (e.g., Python, MATLAB) and project management skills are strong advantages. Teaching experiences in the related fields are a plus. Documented expertise and working experience within at least one of the following research and educational areas is of great advantage:
Machine learning and statistics,
Big data analytics,
Digital signal processing,
Application of these technologies in more than one different area, e.g., in e-health, physics, mechanical engineering and robotics.
Excellent written and oral communication skills in English are required. Swedish skills are a plus. Teamwork experiences should also be documented in the application. Since the subject is male dominated, we encourage female applicants.
Applicants will be selected through a qualitative overall assessment of the competences and skills, assessed most suitable to conduct research and to contribute to the successful development of the research environment.
Further information Please contact:
Head of research, Prof. Welf Löwe, +46 470 708495, welf.lowe@lnu.se
Head of department, Assoc.-Prof. Morgan Ericsson, +46 470 767872, morgan.ericsson@lnu.se
Human Resources Consultant, Emmy Andersson, +46 480 446108 emmy.andersson@lnu.se
Welcome with your application before February 10th, 2023

Linnaeus University has the ambition to utilize the qualities that an even gender distribution and diversity brings to the organization.

Please apply by clicking on the Apply button at the bottom of the ad. Your application should be designed according to the Template for application which can be found in the Guide to Appointment procedures under important documents below the ad. The credentials you invoke must be verified with certification and they must be attached digitally in your application. Other documents, including various types of scientific works, must be submitted digitally along with the application. The application and other documents to be marked with the reference number. All documents cited must be received by the University no later than 24.00 (Local time in Sweden) on the closing day.
