Title: Information & Integration Architect to Polestar
Description:
We are currently looking for an Integration & Information Architect to join our team.

Let us describe the challenge we offer
To allow our product teams to build world-class customer experiences on a global market we need a common map of our information assets and how it flows between our systems. As the Integration & Information Architect you will enable this by working with the teams to define the policies and standards for how we design, use and exchange information in our system landscape, and ensure that such standards are followed by the teams.

What you'll do
You will work in a team of architects covering enterprise architecture, software quality, technical standards and information & integration architecture. The team is oriented under the Deputy CDO and supports all the product domains and stakeholders across the organization. Our mindset is very focused on business outcome and being an embedded part of our delivery organization.

Other tasks you will be accountable for:
Design, develop and govern integration architecture principles to secure best practice architecture
Enable effective data and analytics governance, develop information governance processes and structures, as well as sources and classifications – in close collaboration with the Information Security and Data & Analytics teams
Conduct business information modelling, create and manage business information models in all forms - including conceptual models, database designs, message models and others.
Have the responsibility to document the information/data flow and communication between systems.
Act as an architecture evangelist, active in forums, working groups, functional and regional areas to ensure that communication and alignment is maintained.
Enhance decision-making and provide the organization with a view of the information landscape for strategic planning etc.
Improve business performance through enterprise information solutions and capabilities (master data management, metadata management, analytics, content management, data integration, and related information management or information infrastructure components
Operational work planning cross organizational projects and tasks enabling solutions working End-to-End
Proactively advice in architecture governance forums and design authorities for design decisions
Document and govern architecture documentation artifacts
Contribute to strategy development in alignment with the roadmaps of system vendors
Who you are
We are looking for you, who is a team player with great collaboration and communication skills. You have the ability to find great solutions through collaboration with different teams. You are self-driven and engaged with a will to encourage people as well as resilient and result-driven with a persuasive, flexible, and passionate personality. Moreover, you are a natural problem solver with a detailed focus and are known as a completer/finisher.
To be a great fit for this position we believe you have:
Have a relevant background with 10+ years of experience in information architecture, integration architecture and solution design
Experience in working with microservices based architecture in a cloud-based environment (AWS)
Have an End-to-End process mindset, bridging between solution areas and applications to integration with standard and best practices as guiding principles
Experience in design and governance of Cloud based solutions in a hybrid scenario with on premise solutions
Knowledge of ERP landscape, process architecture and the ERP application portfolio
Ability to translate business requirements into integration architecture requirements, roadmap and deliverable.
As the Information & Integration Architect, you will collaborate with the product domains in their implementation through guiding and coaching. You are also responsible for documenting our landscape and provide visualization of our information assets and flows. Since Polestar’s in a scale-up phase you thrive by working in a fast-paced environment.
People at Polestar
We know that a change is needed. We also know that each one of us can help bring about that change. Our commitment to becoming climate-neutral by 2040 is just as important to us as being inclusive, diverse, and innovative. Together, we are creating, collaborating and experimenting to usher in a new era of sustainable mobility.
We are an electric performance brand, determined to improve the society we live in.
Is this you? If you are interested in joining the Polestar family, don't wait with submitting your application. We apply a continuous selection process and the job post will be open until the position is filled.

Are you ready for the journey? Which is electric by the way...

#LI-VS1

Title: Senior Solution Architect
Description:
Senior Solution Architect
Do you have expertise in, and passion for, Architecture? Would you like to apply your expertise to impact a company that follows the science and turns ideas into life changing medicines? If so, AstraZeneca might be the one for you!
ABOUT ASTRAZENECA
AstraZeneca is a global, innovation-driven BioPharmaceutical business that focuses on the discovery, development and commercialisation of prescription medicines for some of the world’s most serious disease. But we’re more than one of the world’s leading pharmaceutical companies.
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
ABOUT THE ROLE?
The Senior Solution Architect is accountable for determining and architecting solutions that enable the desired business capabilities, delivering in alignment with AstraZeneca’s IT strategy, roadmap, principles and standards. They work with other Solution Architects in the Manufacturing domain and experience in this domain is essential.
The Senior Solution Architect ensures that AZ technical solutions are delivered to AZ defined reference architecture and technology standards, and this includes the definition of such standards where there are capability gaps. The role will ensure that common architecture decisions are implemented consistently across the business and IT.
The role will provide Information Technology architectural expertise and technical direction to system development and integration projects. The Architect will work on architectures for business solutions and will specialise in at least one architecture domain, with the aligned domain for this role being the Manufacturing domain within the Operations group.
ABOUT OUR IT ARCHITECTURE TEAM

As Architects, we connect the dots across the business to improve the agility and functionality of our processes to accelerate AstraZeneca to the next level. There’s so much potential to influence and inspire change, it’s a big challenge if you’re up for it. As champions of our Technology ecosystem, we make sure the rest of the business experiences the true benefits of our systems. Uniting diverse areas and simplifying the way we work, changing approaches and behaviours along the way – our reach goes beyond technology. It starts with a holistic view, connecting emerging trends with business ambitions and applying emotional intelligence to understand how we can guide the right way to work and behave. Across the enterprise and each technology domain we come together to find leading solutions that will provide the platform for AstraZeneca’s success. Change agents, we are always proactively hunting for new insights and problem-solving to identify better ways of doing things. Motivated by the opportunities to learn and grow, we move fast and drive forward. Lay the foundations for future technological and people-driven success across AstraZeneca.
Candidate Focus & Challenge
Senior Solution Architect for IGNITE: Operations IT (MAKE) Architecture
This role is accountable for the solution architecture and design across AstraZeneca’s Operations domains eg Manufacturing & Supply Chain with a focus on Data & Analytics capabilities.
You will be the responsible architect on projects within areas including but not limited to: Smart Factory, Digital Uplift, Digital Transformation and Lifecycle Refresh Programmes. You will be required to analyse, conceptualise, design and govern across AstraZeneca’s strategic IT landscape to in order to support business projects.
Accountable for architecting and designing comprehensive solutions that meet business requirements and are aligned to AstraZeneca’s Enterprise Architecture, in support of a given portfolio
Design architectures and delivers documentation for projects or solutions in order to address business/application/data/infrastructure requirements
Ensure that solution architectures and designs are appropriately robust and address business, application, information and infrastructure architectural requirements
Ensure analysis and design is documented in supporting Architectural Artefacts ie Solution Blueprint and seeks Architecture Review Board Signoff.
Work with Business Analysis and Solution Engineering functions to support functional & technical requirements management, including providing senior architecture support in key processes including technology acquisition
Partner with project managers, business analysts, and solution engineers to create solutions that are aligned to AstraZeneca architecture standards and principles, leverage common solutions and services, and meet the financial targets (cost and benefits)
Support the Enterprise Architect in defining technology roadmaps.
Within the solution development lifecycle, the role will be accountable for solution evaluation and selection, buy vs. build decisions, and early-phase project estimates which contribute to a given case
Provide technical & IT expertise support to project teams and conducts AZ architectural reviews throughout project lifecycle
Ensure compliance with existing EA guidelines and standards (e.g. AZ Architecture Engagement Process (ISPMM) and EA Software Standards)
Contribute to project and service teams in the development, implementation and maintenance of standard architectural components
Work with third party suppliers as required and contributes to the creation of functional design documents
Work with third party suppliers to verify technical development and delivery are in alignment with the Architecture Roadmap
Contribute to the development of the Architecture Capability by documenting and sharing knowledge and standard methodologies with peer Architects
ESSENTIAL SKILLS & EXPERIENCE REQUIRED?
Proven experience of application solution architecture and design experience, with proven capability in data & analytics, AI/ML application architecture and exposure to working in an operations domain, i.e.; manufacturing, supply chain etc.
Relevant technical degree or equivalent
Proven skills and experience being the solution architect on projects and programmes
Experience of Operations domains and processes
Technologies: Relational, Column Store Databases, Big Data technologies, data streaming, real-time inference, Front end tooling PowerBI, QlikSense, Data Science Tooling - SageMaker and other similar platforms, manufacturing system technologies including MES, Historian, OPC
Proven development/design experience in at least one technical domain
Experience of developing innovative solutions, blueprints and standards for solution design
Experience implementing and maintaining business solution architectures under any formal framework for their domain of architecture
Experience of developing and managing relationships with 3rd party suppliers
Excellent analytical skills
Excellent communication, facilitation and relationship management skills
Strong networking skills with good internal/external links
Ability to interpret and communicate technical information into business language
Evidence of shaping innovative solutions that have a major impact within the business area and organisation
Excellent business acumen and strong knowledge of procurement business processes
Demonstrated initiative, strong customer orientation, and cross-cultural working
Experience working in a global organization where partners and project team members are geographically dispersed
Ability to travel to AstraZeneca’s global Operations sites
Ability to work well in diverse, multinational teams and proven ability to influence others to achieve positive outcomes
WHY JOIN IT?
We’re a network of entrepreneurial self-starters who contribute to something far bigger. There’s a diversity of expertise in our Technology group that’s unique to AstraZeneca – it allows us to dive deep into exploring new groundbreaking technology. We enable AstraZeneca to perform at its peak by delivering world-class technology and data solutions. Our work unlocks the potential of science. We optimise and evolutionise AstraZeneca by maximising efficiencies and finding new ways to drive productivity. From automation to data simplification. We’re not afraid to take ownership and run with it. Empowered with unrivalled freedom. A place to be open and transparent – we speak up, think creatively and share ideas. Our diverse contributions help us to make better decisions. But we have a constant drive to innovate, and an appreciation for high standards. It takes challenging the status quo to contribute in our ever-evolving environment. We love it here because put simply, we make a meaningful impact.
Technology at AstraZeneca is a home for purposeful disruptors!
SO, WHAT’S NEXT?
Are you already imagining yourself joining our team? Good, because we’d love to hear from you! Click the link to apply and we’ll be in touch as soon as we can.
WHERE CAN I FIND OUT MORE?
Our Social Media, Follow AstraZeneca on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/1603/
Follow AstraZeneca on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/astrazenecacareers/
Follow AstraZeneca on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/astrazeneca_careers/?hl=en
Competitive salary & benefits on offer.
Close Date: 5/2/2023

Title: Software Development Line Manager
Description:
At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.
Jeppesen, a subsidiary of The Boeing Company, is one of the largest software development companies in Gothenburg. We develop innovative optimization solutions for the world’s leading airlines. We are dedicated to continuous improvement, delivering more value to our clients, and exploring emerging technologies such as quantum computing, AI and big data analytics.
At Jeppesen’s office in central Gothenburg you will work in a one-of-a-kind software development organization with fascinating solutions that make a real difference to people around the world. You will be working in an agile learning organization, surrounded by a team of talented, creative and dedicated colleagues. You will learn and broaden your perspective by working with 400 professionals from more than 30 different nations, but also be part of a global organization allowing for collaboration with customers and colleagues across the world. Most importantly, you will be expected to make a difference.

Are you up for a Challenge?
We are looking for passionate leaders who want to join us and our journey to build world-class software development teams.
We are now strengthening and expanding our Software Development Line Management team to meet our growing business and to accelerate our journey towards DevSecOps and SaaS.
We are seeking a Software Development Line Manager to join Gothenburg office.

Responsibilities:
As a line Manager you will be accountable for the work done in your agile development teams. You and your teams will innovate, develop, maintain and support software that helps the airline industry to solve some of the most complex optimization problems in the world.

As a line Manager you are accountable for the software delivery performance of your teams and you will take part in and drive work to improve existing processes and frameworks. You will work tightly with product management to make sure we meet the business demands, commitments and improvement objectives.

You will also play an important part in working with the strategic objectives for the department. Stretching your skills when it comes to facilitation, collaboration, growth mindset and problem solving.
We look for people who are passionate about building highly effective teams.
To build the most advanced optimization software for Crew and Network Operations we need to attract and develop the best talent. Our leaders play an important role in nurturing our identity and company culture. We want our teams to apply an owner’s mentality in everything they do and to feel proud about what they do for our customers. This requires a special mindset and we believe our leaders play an important role in building and nurturing that culture.

As a Leader we believe that you:
Have a background in the IT industry
Have a track record of being a good coach to teams and people
Are passionate about always improving ways of working and that you are eager to learn
Are passionate about software development and new technology
Are familiar with Agile and Lean principles
Have track record of creating a safe, inclusive and collaborative working climate
Required competence:
Fluent in English
Do you want to be a part of building the best optimization solutions in the world?
Our office has an international atmosphere based on diversity, trust and inclusion. You will notice this culture in the dedication our teams put into building the best Crew & Network solutions possible. To sustain this culture and to build effective teams, we need skilled leaders who emulate the servant leadership philosophy and who are able to build an inspiring work environment.
We hope you are curios to learn more about us, and that you want to join our fantastic crew.

Please apply by sending your CV in English.
Employer will not sponsor applicants for employment visa status.

Important information regarding this requisition: Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense. This requisition is for an international, locally hired position in Sweden. Successful candidates must be able to obtain and maintain legal authorization to work in Sweden for continued employment. Benefits and pay are determined at the local level and are not part of Boeing U.S. based payroll.
Relocation:
This position does not offer relocation. Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense.

Equal Opportunity Employer:
We are an equal opportunity employer. We do not accept unlawful discrimination in our recruitment or employment practices on any grounds including but not limited to; color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, physical or mental disability, genetic factors, military and veteran status, or other characteristics covered by applicable law.
We have teams in more than 65 countries, and each person plays a role in helping us become one of the world’s most innovative, diverse and inclusive companies. Applicants are encouraged to share with our recruitment team any accommodations required during the recruitment process.

Title: Videogames Streaming Engineer
Description:
Sweden
SEK 40,000 to SEK 55,000 SEK
Developer Role
Skills: Node.js, React.js, Linux, Docker, AWS, Lambda
Level: Mid-level

Videogames Streaming Engineer
ONM07/12_1670431862
Job Description

A world-renowned games streaming company is looking to hire!

As they plan to scale up their tech team ahead of some very exciting new developments in 2023, they are beginning their search now, so as to get ahead of the inevitable hiring rush coming in January.

Role & Responsibilities

Design, build and deploy node-based microservices into a petascale cloud infrastructure streaming games and to millions of users across the world
Tackling challenges associated with the streaming sector; framerate optimisation, upscaling resolution, audio/video compressions, and the total removal of any lag in the platform
Taking part in an active R&D project wherein the team plans to implement big data analytics, in mind to transition towards neural networks for predicting player actions

2+ years of professional experience working with distributed networks (either Linux based, or cloud-hosted)

Benefits

Hardware allowance, wellness allowance

Title: Sales Executive
Description:
Who we are
We are an early-stage startup hell-bent on improving the post-purchase experience in the e-commerce industry, starting with the biggest pain point: returns. We move fast and expect a lot because we're working on something that will truly make the e-commerce industry more sustainable, financially and environmentally. With COVID19 crisis accelerating the migration from offline to online, together with booming acquisition costs, increasing customer loyalty has become paramount. At the same time, with increasing online sales, retailers suffer from booming returns.
yayloh is a SaaS solution for e-commerce retailers, which digitalizes and automates the return process and unleashes the potential of return data. yayloh will increase customer satisfaction and loyalty while improving retailers profitability and reducing environmental impact. Using data analytics and applied machine learning, yayloh allows e-commerce retailers to understand their customers needs on an advanced level. yayloh is backed by the early-stage VC Antler. Also worth mentioning, we have happy customers and a growing pipeline in different countries!
What we’re looking for
We are looking for our first sales champion! This is a key position for the company and you will work closely with the founding team, reporting to the CEO.
We are looking for someone who has experience working in B2B SaaS sales, ideally in the e-commerce industry. You can initiate and close deals, help improve our sales process and empathize with our customers to relate their needs to our product team. Before the team grows, you will need to be very hands-on and take care of your customers’ support and success.
Ideally, you have the potential to grow in this position and further manage a team that you will help to recruit, onboard and coach to reach the stars!

Responsibilities
Ownership of the full sales cycle from lead to close
Prospect relentlessly to build your pipeline: cold calling/emailing, working network, sourcing referrals, attending shows, maintaining relationships with lost opportunities
Educate potential clients in the services and values provided by yayloh
Establish lasting relationships with senior executives and decision-makers
Maintain detailed documentation of leads and contribute to improving data accuracy in Hubspot CRM
Be a team player and identify improvement areas in yayloh’s sales process, offering and strategy
Remain the first point of contact for our customers after sale and support onboarding process
Advocate on behalf of customers, bridging conversations between client requirements and development teams
Must-haves
Be social, enjoy reaching out to people. Experienced with and excited to do cold calling/emailing
5+ years of experience opening, negotiating, and closing B2B SaaS deals in the e-commerce industry
Sustained success in acquiring new business or customer acquisition
Ability to manage multiple opportunities simultaneously at various stages of the buying process
Strong analytics and strategic thinking. Result-driven as well as excellent interpersonal and collaborative skills, able to thrive in a fast-paced environment
Excellent communication skills in English and Swedish
The dream team
We are international from day-one with a co-founding team from France and India and English is the company language so everyone feels included. Our first market is the Nordics but we dream big and are building a global company.
We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters so we don’t see failures but learning opportunities. Innovation is at the heart of everything we do and we believe anything is possible when you can think freely, without boundaries nor pre-set frameworks.
We don’t count your hours and you can work from your couch if this is where you perform the best, what we will care about is how many happy customers will join our tribe thanks to you!

How to apply?
Send Resume and short intro email to sophie@yayloh.com

Title: DBA till vårt team i Stockholm
Description:
Just nu söker vi dig i rollen som DBA som motiveras av att få möjligheten av att arbeta med erfarna kolleger och som vill ta del av spännande uppdrag hos våra kunder.
Till vår avdelning DBA i Stockholm söker vi dig som nu är redo för ditt nästa steg och vill vara med på vår resa med att växa internationellt. Totalt kommer vi löpande rekrytera 3 st till denna roil under 2023
Varför börja arbeta hos oss?
Hos oss på Cegal/SQL Service arbetar branschens bästa inom SQL Server.
Cegal/SQL Service är ett bolag med fokus på Data management och Data Analytics. Vi levererar konsulttjänster inom alla branscher, men även support och drifttjänster.
Våra medarbetare är stolta och passionerade över sitt arbete. Hos oss får du jobba med några av de bästa databaskonsulterna i Sverige och får möjligheten att accelerera din kompetensökning.
Om rollen

Title: Doctoral position in analysis of adolescents' exposure to food marketing and associated obesity/related lifestyle habits
Description:
The Department of Biosciences and Nutrition performs research and education in several areas of medical sciences including cancer biology, aging, molecular endocrinology, functional genomics, systems biology, structural biology, protein biochemistry, immunology, and nutrition. It offers an excellent international research and working environment, including around 200 scientists, students, administrative and technical personnel. The Department resides in Neo at Campus Flemingsberg, a biomedical research building, aimed at being a creative and open environment that enables meetings, synergies, and exploration of areas of mutual interest across disciplines
Do you want to contribute to improving human health?
To be a doctoral student means to devote oneself to a research project under supervision of experienced researchers and following an individual study plan. For a doctoral degree, the equivalent of four years of full-time doctoral education is required.
The research group
We are looking for a PhD student n nutrition and technology-assisted behavioral measurements to work within the IMPACT research group (Innovative use of Mobile Phones to promote physical ACTivity and nutrition across the life span) that is led by Professor Marie Löf. The PhD project will be realized within the Work Unit of Researcher Ioannis Ioakeimidis which has a wide research interest, spanning from clinical studies to real world data analytics, focusing on the use of novel technologies to monitor health-related behaviors and support behavioral change. The PhD project will focus on the Unit's obesity/related research with adolescents' behaviors and living environment, in association with school life and environment. This will combine tasks within the domains of eHealth/technology-assisted research, real-world behavioral and ecological studies, as well as qualitative research activities.
The doctoral student project and the duties of the doctoral student
This PhD project aims to investigate children's exposure to unhealthy food marketing, including physical and digital food advertising. Furthermore, it will investigate associations between exposure to food advertising, intake of unhealthy foods during and after school hours, school lunch skipping and other health-related adolescents' behaviours. In the long term, the project aims to identify possible intervention strategies aiming at facilitating healthier eating habits for adolescents, related with school-life and beyond. Specifically, the project will have two methodological approaches. Initially, the quantitative component of the project will include objective behavioural data collection through purpose-built smartphone apps and other related wearable sensors. The parallel qualitative component of the project will entail the description of students' and teacher attitudes and opinions about the effects of food marketing on adolescents' lifestyle, as well as about potential solutions to such social challenges.

The successful PhD applicant will be involved in real-world, school-based studies towards these goals. The planned effort includes iterative methodological evaluations, an observational behavioural monitoring study and parallel qualitative data collection. The student will be involved in all steps of the research project, i.e., planning, developing the study protocol and content, writing ethical applications, data collection and analysis, writing manuscripts and publishing the study outcomes. The planned data analysis will require development of methodological automations for data pre-processing and formatting and performance of analyses using R. Mobile app and software testing are also important tasks within this framework. Finally, the student will be involved within pedagogical responsibilities of the research group on Bachelor and Master's levels in KI.

What do we offer?
A creative and inspiring environment full of expertise and curiosity. Karolinska Institutet is one of the world's leading medical universities. Our vision is to pursue the development of knowledge about life and to promote a better health for all. At Karolinska Institutet, we conduct successful medical research and hold the largest range of medical education in Sweden. As a doctoral student you are offered an individual research project, a well-educated supervisor, a vast range of elective courses and the opportunity to work in a leading research group. Karolinska Institutet collaborates with prominent universities from all around the world, which ensures opportunities for international exchanges. You will be employed on a doctoral studentship which means that you receive a contractual salary. Employees also have access to our modern gym for free and receive reimbursements for medical care.
Eligibility requirements for doctoral education
In order to participate in the selection for a doctoral position, you must meet the following general (A) and specific (B) eligibility requirements at latest by the application deadline.
It is your responsibility to certify eligibility by following the instructions on the web page Entry requirements (eligibility) for doctoral education.


A) General eligibility requirement

You meet the general eligibility requirement for doctoral/third-cycle/PhD education if you:
have been awarded a second-cycle/advanced/master qualification (i.e. master degree), or
have satisfied the requirements for courses comprising at least 240 credits of which at least 60 credits were awarded in the advanced/second-cycle/master level, or
have acquired substantially equivalent knowledge in some other way in Sweden or abroad.*
Follow the instructions on the web page Entry requirements (eligibility) for doctoral education.
If you claim equivalent knowledge, follow the instructions on the web page Assessing equivalent knowledge for general eligibility for doctoral education.

B) Specific eligibility requirement
You meet the specific eligibility requirement for doctoral/third-cycle/PhD education if you:
Show proficiency in English equivalent to the course English B/English 6 at Swedish upper secondary school.
Follow the instructions on the web page English language requirements for doctoral education.
Verification of your documents Karolinska Institutet checks the authenticity of your documents. Karolinska Institutet reserves the right to revoke admission if supporting documents are discovered to be fraudulent. Submission of false documents is a violation of Swedish law and is considered grounds for legal action.
(A) and (B) can only be certified by the documentation requirement for doctoral education.
Skills and personal qualities
For this position a solid background in nutrition or similar is required. The candidate should have strong communication skills and a proven ability to interact with Swedish school children of different ages, as well as Swedish school personnel. Fluent knowledge of English, both oral and written, is a requirement. Previous experience with quantitative and qualitative data collection within the domain of nutritional science is a requirement. Experience with such research with children and especially in school settings will be highly appreciated. Previous experience evaluating and implementing eHealth tools and platforms (e.g., smartphones, web-based portals etc.) for data collection is a strong merit. Previous work with picture analysis is also a merit, especially with regards to food type analytics. Past publications (e.g., scientific papers, public health reports, public health action plans, etc.) will be appreciated. We are looking for a student who can work independently and at the same time collaborate well with others. Emphasis will be placed on personal suitability,
Terms and conditions
The doctoral student will be employed on a doctoral studentship maximum 4 years full-time.
-[Video about Karolinska Institutet, how we all work towards "a better health for all"] -
Application process
Submit your application and supporting documents through the Varbi recruitment system. Use the button in the top right corner and follow the instructions. We prefer that your application is written in English, but you can also apply in Swedish.
Your application must contain the following documents:
A personal letter and a curriculum vitae
Degree projects and previous publications, if any
Any other documentation showing the desirable skills and personal qualities described above
Documents certifying your general eligibility (see A above)
Documents certifying your specific eligibility (see B above)
Selection
A selection will be made among eligible applicants on the basis of the ability to benefit from doctoral education. The qualifications of the applicants will be evaluated on an overall basis.
Karolinska Institutet uses the following bases of assessment:
Documented subject knowledge of relevance to the area of research
Analytical skill
Other documented knowledge or experience that may be relevant to doctoral studies in the subject.
All applicants will be informed when the recruitment is completed.
Links;
www.bionut.ki.se
https://ki.se/en/bionut/the-impact-research-group-marie-lof

Title: Analyitcs Engineer

Collaborate with stakeholders to collect business requirements and define successful analytics outcomes

Demonstrated ability to design, build and maintain complex data services
Proficient at building datasets that are accurate and easy to understand and consume
Spark in Scala and/or Python
SQL and Relational Databases
Ability to be committed to the end result and help others gets there

Fast learner, self-starter and intellectually curious
Fluent in English
Willing to learn, or already know, basic Swedish

Experience shaping and evolving data architecture
Knowledge of one or more business domains
Based near Stockholm, Gothenburg or Malmö (or willing to relocate).
Bonus points for:

Experience building data and analytics organizations
Knowledge of advanced statistical analysis techniques
Familiar or skilled with machine learning
Why join us?
Interesting and forward-looking assignments within fintechs, e-commerce companies and digital startups / scale-ups
Collaborative, transparent, creative and fun loving culture which you will be involved in shaping
Opportunities for personal and professional growth
Investment in your competence development in latest skills & technologies
An international team (including our partner network) ~6 nationalities so far
Competitive salary
Learning & sharing environment - colleagues skilled in their areas and that enjoy knowledge sharing
Have a mid/long term plan of becoming a freelancer? We'd like to be a part of that and help you towards that goal.
Company parties & team activities
How to apply
If you fit the description above, we’d love to hear from you!
Job Type: Full-time
Salary: From 50,000.00kr per month

Title: Senior C# Developer
Description:
Would you like to contribute to healthy and comfortable indoor environments for people to be at their best and at the same time work with products that have a positive impact on the environment? Then this is the perfect opportunity!
“At Swegon, I get to work with tasks that are developing for me together with wonderful colleagues” – Niclas Zettervall, R&D Engineer

“In a self-organizing group, I get the opportunity to develop and contribute with what I do best” - Vedran Lipovac, Scrummaster

“All my colleagues are awesome, nice and they are truly passionate with what they do. All of this is contagious and it is incredibly inspiring to work here. Apart from that, I have a manager who gives me continuously feedback” – Shiva Fadaei Heydari, System Developer Digital Service
What will you be doing?
Joining our Digital service team is all about driving the exciting work to make sure that our products can connect to and use the benefits of internet. Where the physical product end and cloud begins, our work also begin. You will have an important part and impact in an interesting journey since the building industry is currently in a digital transformation that will make the operation of building more data driven, efficient and thereby sustainable. Data sharing between systems is vital for efficient resources use and an optimal indoor environmental comfort and energy performance of buildings.
We work in close cooperation with the different business units within Swegon. The team covers many disciplines from connectivity in the products, to cloud functions and services for the users. On a daily basis, you would work with the cloud part of our solution developed in C#, ASP.NET Core and ensure that Swegon have a continuous digital services for our products.
You will be part of an agile and motivated software development team with five competent colleagues. Together you will develop and optimize functions within your area. This position is a hybrid remote and will be based in Gothenburg. Some travelling withing Europe is very likely, depending on your interest.
What’s in it for you?
We offer an open-minded and fun environment full of highly skilled people with whom you can constantly develop yourself. This job is a great opportunity for someone who wants to have the possibility to be part of a strategic, long term and growing team. Digitalization and sustainability are vital parts in almost everything we do, and the products we work with really make a difference. Due to the fact that Swegon participates in many industry networks that drives a unified way of describing properties for property owners, you will have a possibility to influence industry standards.
Who are you?
You are driven by curiosity within your profession, have the flexibility to easy adapt to changing circumstances and sees the opportunities in change. You have the ability to think outside the box and find new solutions. Apart from that, you really strives to find the best win-win solutions and is agile and responsive in relation with others. You thrives with and are used to working agile
In addition to curiosity and creativity, we are looking for you that have:
Proven work experience from REST APIs
At least a bachelor's degree in relevant studies
Proven work experience in Microsoft Azure
At least fiver years of relevant work experience
Fluent in English or Swedish, preferably both
Work permit in Sweden
We also value if you have experience, familiarity or interest with some of the below:
SQL databases, React, Cloud architecture, data analytics.
If all of this describes who you are, we might just be fit for each other.
How do you apply?
Apply for this job via www.swegon.se/jobb no later than January 31th. If you have any questions, please reach out to our System Development Director, Digital Services John Wibrand john.wibrand@swegon.com.
We offer
At Swegon we want people to feel good inside. We supply products and services for a healthy indoor climate, with solutions for ventilation, heating, cooling and climate optimization. We are also at the forefront of our industry in making sure good indoor climate does not come at the expense of the outdoor climate – energy efficient operation and sustainability throughout production is at the core of what we do. To guide us on our way, we have our core values – Customer Empathy, Trust and Commitment – which sets the culture of Swegon. This means a strong belief in delegated decision making, a drive to be the best at what we do and the necessary collegial support to solve the tasks at hand – in short, it’s a place to grow professionally and as a person. We also believe it’s vital to be able to combine work life and personal life, providing flexibility when possible. In recruiting, we place great emphasis on a finding people with the right attitude, and greater diversity and improved gender equality is one of our most important strategic targets.
Do you want to be part of our journey? We look forward to hearing from you!
If you are looking to sell consultant, please don´t contact us. We are looking for a fulltime person employed by us.
About us
Swegon Group AB, owned by Investment AB Latour, listed on the Stockholm Stock Exchange, is a market leading supplier in the field of indoor environment, offering solutions for ventilation, heating, cooling and climate optimisation, as well as connected services and expert technical support. Swegon has subsidiaries in and distributors all over the world and 19 production plants in Europe, North America and India. The company employs close to 3 000 people and in 2021 had a turnover of 5,8 billion SEK.
We kindly and firmly decline any direct contact with staffing and recruitment companies as well as purveyors of additional job ads.

Title: Senior Business Analyst (Senior Compliance Officer)
Description:
Would you like to be part of an international team where you get to use your programme management experience? If you are looking for a role within Anti Money Laundering and Counter Terrorist Financing and enjoy handling complex projects and fast-paced initiatives, this is a great opportunity for you.
Before you continue... Don’t meet every requirement?
Danske Bank and this team are committed to a diverse, inclusive and authentic workforce – so if you´re excited by this role and think you have most, but not all, requirements, we encourage you to still apply – you may just be the perfect candidate.

Your future team across the Nordics

We are looking for a Senior Business Analyst / Junior Project Manager (Senior Compliance Officer) to work in our Programme Office within FCC Data & Analytics. This unit is responsible for the oversight and management of centralised data analytics, solution development and MI reporting for FCC. It is part of a wider function responsible for the overseeing and ensuring compliance with monitoring of transactions and customers for financial crime activity related to Money Laundering, Terrorist Financing and Tax Evasion, investigating unusual and suspicious activity and undertaking analytics and reporting activities for the wider FCC group.
The team has employees across the Nordics and this position can be based in Stockholm, Copenhagen or Helsinki.
As a business analyst, you will handle and support a range of different operational, technology and analysis projects ongoing within the team as well as working with a large range of stakeholders to build & optimise capabilities to support detection, investigation and prevention of financial crime.

As the team is distributed across several countries, we operate with a high level of autonomy and trust, and you are responsible for managing your own workday around the deliveries you are responsible for.

Innovative environment

We expect that you have significant business analyst experience with project management experience a benefit to your application. You will also demonstrate a strong capability to independently handle multiple projects in parallel within an innovative environment that requires urgent solutions and in-depth analysis under significant time pressure.
You will be comfortable working with stakeholders from both business and IT teams and supporting an end-to-end project lifecycle. Experience of working with, use, or development of technology & visualisation solutions to support data analysis projects would be a bonus.

Excellent written and spoken English is required. We are open to candidates who come from a variety of backgrounds and are interested in the overall skillset you bring to the table. Knowledge of Financial Crime is not essential as you will receive training but is desirable.

We expect you to be structured in your approach to your work, be able to flexibly operate in a fast-moving environment and take pride in delivering high quality work. Due to the nature of our work, we expect a high degree of integrity and ability to comply with our responsibility of confidentiality.
You will have a valid working visa or right to work in Nordic countries, as this role will not sponsor visa applications.

Interested?

If you have any questions, you are welcome to contact the Head of FCC D&A, Ross Pudney by email ( pud@danskebank.se ) or Julie Refnov, Head of FCC D&A Programme Office by email ( jref@danskebank.dk ).
We will be reviewing candidates as we receive applications. The last day for your application, 29 th of January.

Title: Product Design Lead
Description:
About the team
The Product team at Accedo has a mission to create a scalable platform for building impactful video applications. With Accedo One, our award-winning product, our customers are able to set up their own video streaming apps, without any additional development. We are passionate about making advanced functionality easily accessible to our customers by innovative user experiences.
We’re now looking for a Design Lead to join our growing team. As a Design Lead, you will be part of the Product Management team and will work closely with our existing UI/UX designers as well as our Product Owners. Due to Covid-19 and the associated impossibility for relocations, for now we can only accept applicants who hold a valid work permit or are eligible to work in Sweden.

What you will do
As a Design Lead, you will play a key role in conceptualizing, planning, designing products that will be used by some of the most distinguished media brands in the world. You will craft products from existing ideas and develop new ideas based on your market research, industry experiences, and the product vision.
Your work will be focused on Accedo One, our platform to grow and transform video experiences. Accedo One comprises cloud management products and app development products. You will work with our colleagues mainly in Sweden and Hungary, to initiate and drive cohesive design strategies, including admin panel design and multi-platform app designs (across Desktop, Mobile, Tablet, TV). Accedo One and its products are used every day by customers and developers around the world. Millions of users every day are enjoying video apps configured through Accedo One.

Primary Responsibilities:
Your key responsibilities will be:
Designing intuitive, innovative and delightful user experiences for our back-office admin panel products and video app templates and design
Working collaboratively within the Agile process with other UX designers, product owners and developers
Leading and mentoring supporting Design team members both in day-to-day work and long-term skills development and career path
Creating user flows, personas, user stories and combine them into directive guidelines to other designers and developers
Creating hands-on UI
Leveraging data/analytics, as available, to make decisions
Developing a deep understanding of the Accedo’s customers and their needs

What we are looking for
A design-related diploma or degree
5+ years of experience working with design for mobile/tv/web apps and/or back office admin panels
2+ years of experience working as the lead for a team of designers
Strong knowledge of Figma or similar tools
Excellent communication skills and being fluent in English
Excellent understanding of UX principles
Excellent problem solving skills and a love for UX challenges
Have a positive attitude, is self-motivated and able to multitask
Ability to learn new tools and guidelines quickly
Enjoy keeping up-to-date with the latest UI trends, techniques, and technologies
Experience in user research is a plus

What we offer
Competitive salary and benefits
Yearly training budget (which can be spent on conferences or online training)
Nice, spacious downtown office in the hip neighbourhood of Södermalm
Flexible home office options
Opportunity to participate in Hackathons and a range of company events

About Accedo
We are Accedo and have more than ten years of experience helping hundreds of TV platform operators, broadcasters, media companies, and consumer electronics manufacturers across the globe to design, deliver and manage the next generation video user experience across a vast range of connected devices. Accedo delivers rich media apps on multiple platforms ranging from Smart TVs, gaming consoles and media devices to smartphones and tablets, and for customers such as Netflix, Spotify, BBC, HBO and Deutsche Telekom, just to name a few.
Accedo offers a truly global working environment, with offices all over the world, including Stockholm, Budapest, London, New York, Toronto, Sydney, and Hong Kong, amongst others. Our global team is exceptionally talented, dedicated and fun! Sounds interesting? Come join our family and become a fellow Accedonian!

Title: System Reliability Engineer
Description:

You can expect an autonomous but fast-paced work environment where you are recognized for your results and ability to drive things forward. Every day brings many opportunities to learn & grow and rewards with the global impact we create.

Be part of all activities regarding our applications, such as the handling of incoming issues, incident solving, requirements, and launching of new releases.
Design, plan and deploy changes to our existing systems, as well as implement new solutions.

Title: Senior Flutter-utvecklare
Description:
Som Mobile Developer hos oss jobbar du som konsult, och just nu söker vi dig som vill jobba specifikt inom Flutter-utveckling.

Om Hackberry

Hackberry är ett IT-konsultbolag som primärt bygger mobilappar, men vi jobbar även mycket med back-end system, UX-design & Data Analytics. Vi växer just nu mer än någonsin och har precis blivit 22 personer på kontoret! Hackberry är ett rätt ungt företag som vi bygger från grunden, vilket ger oss en fantastisk möjlighet att skapa ett innovativt företag som passar den moderna konsulten redan från början. Vi vill växa med människor som är peppade på att bygga Hackberry tillsammans med oss. Vårt nya hem är The Factory, som ligger i ett växande område i Sollentuna. Här arbetar vi under samma tak som en mängd andra spännande startups och scaleups.

Vi bygger huvudsakligen appar för våra kunder! Internt eller på plats hos kund, stora som små projekt, i team eller individuellt, hos stora etablerade företag eller nya intressanta startups. Allt är möjligt och allt gör vi. Vi är ett fullservice företag, och kan hantera alla delar av kedjan från idé till koncept, design, UX/UI, utveckling, integration, test, data analytics, support och förvaltning.
Om rollen

Som mobilutvecklare här på Hackberry kommer du att få jobba i många spännande projekt hos olika kunder i varierande storlekar. Dina dagar ser olika ut beroende på vilken kund du är hos, men en dag här är inte en annan dag lik. Varje dag ställs du inför nya komplexa, men spännande problem att lösa.
Din vardag kommer troligtvis innehålla någon av flertalet arbetsuppgifter: Scrum-genomgång, vidareutveckling av koden, lägga till nya features, jobba tillsammans i stimulerande team (både inhouse på vårt kontor & hos kunden), ha kompetenta kollegor att bolla olika lösningar med, ta en fika eller spela en pingsmatch.
Vem vi tror att du är

Vi söker dig som är tidigare arbetat med Flutter. Eftersom vi jobbar som konsulter så är det viktigt att du är flexibel & mångsidig, och att du kan ta dig an nya projekt och miljöer på ett snabbt sätt. Det är även av stor vikt att du kan hantera kunder på ett bra sätt. Vidare har du lätt för att samarbeta med andra människor, är noggrann i din kodning och är kreativ i ditt problemlösning sätt.
Vi förväntar oss att du:
Har minst 3 års arbetslivserfarenhet av Flutter
Talar och skriver obehindrat på svenska
Ser positivt på att kontoret ligger i Sollentuna
Som person är du:
Flexibel
Kreativ
Ansvarstagande
Har en bra samarbetsförmåga
Har en bra problemlösningsförmåga
Har vi fångat ditt intresse?
Skicka in en ansökan redan idag! Urval & intervjuer sker löpande.

Avdelning
Development
Roll
Mobile Developer
Platser
Sollentuna - The Factory
Distansarbete
Hybridarbete

KONTAKT
Alexandra Engman
Head of HR – HR

Title: Erfaren Power BI-utvecklare
Description:
Ellos Group är en ledande e-handelskoncern inom mode, hem och skönhet i Norden. I koncernen ingår e-handelsplatserna Ellos, Jotex och Homeroom. Utöver försäljning i nordiska länderna bedriver vi även e-handel i Polen, Holland, Österrike och Tyskland. Vår verksamhet drivs från Borås där också våra 600 anställda har sin arbetsplats. Totalt omsätter koncernen 3,6 miljarder kronor. Vi strävar ständigt efter att utveckla hållbara erbjudanden för våra kunder. Vi utvecklar och designar egna produkter och vår egen betalningslösning Elpy förser våra kunder med enkla och säkra sätt att genomföra köp på våra plattformar.
www.ellosgroup.se
Har du gedigen erfarenhet som Power BI-utvecklare?
Har du jobbat både med att ta fram komplexa rapporter och att coacha användare i Power BI?
Vet du hur du bygger effektiva laddningar av stora dataset?
Gillar du att röra dig mellan teknik och funktion?

Då kan ditt nästa jobb vara hos oss!
Vi söker en erfaren Power BI-utvecklare till vårt Data Analytics & Reporting/Business Systems team. Vi stödjer hela Ellos Group, d.v.s. Ellos, Jotex och Homeroom med över 2,8 miljoner aktiva kunder. Du kommer således att få jobba med mycket stora transaktionsvolymer. En viktig del i vårt arbetssätt är att vara datadrivna och din roll blir att utveckla och stödja det arbetet. Som Power BI-utvecklare är det därför viktigt att både vara analytisk problemlösare och god kommunikatör.
Den vi söker har flera års erfarenhet av Power BI-utveckling, har byggt dataflöden med stora volymer och optimerat prestanda för dessa. Utöver det är erfarenhet av Data Warehouse-lösningar och ramverk för informationsmodellering (t ex Kimball) starkt meritierande. Likaså erfarenhet av Microsoft-plattformen, SqlServer, SSIS/SSAS/SSRS, Azure. Även erfarenhet av e-handel och rapportering för för ekonomi, inköp, logistik, marknad är intressant.
Viktigast av allt är att du är självgående, ansvarstagande både för leverans och egen utveckling och nyfiken med en ständig vilja att komma framåt. Du blir del av ett gott gäng på vår IT-avdelning med drygt 50 anställda. Vi sitter i Viared/Borås och tillämpar idag ett flexibelt arbetssätt med 3 dagar i veckan på kontoret och 2 dagar i veckan hemifrån.
Låter detta bra? Tveka inte att höra av dig och skicka in med din ansökan!
Har du frågor om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande chef Erik Ehrling på tel 0707-132986
Vi tillämpar löpande urval så skicka gärna din ansökan så snart som möjligt, dock senast den 31 januari.

Title: Scrum master & Test engineer
Description:
At Boeing, we innovate and collaborate to make the world a better place. From the seabed to outer space, you can contribute to work that matters with a company where diversity, equity and inclusion are shared values. We’re committed to fostering an environment for every teammate that’s welcoming, respectful and inclusive, with great opportunity for professional growth. Find your future with us.
Jeppesen, a subsidiary of The Boeing Company, is one of the largest software development companies in Gothenburg. We develop innovative optimization solutions for the world’s leading airlines. We are dedicated to continuous improvement, delivering more value to our clients, and exploring emerging technologies such as quantum computing, AI and big data analytics.
At Jeppesen’s office in central Gothenburg, Sweden you will work in a one-of-a-kind software development organization with fascinating solutions that make a real difference to people around the world. You will be working in an agile learning organization, surrounded by a team of talented, creative and dedicated colleagues. You will learn and broaden your perspective by working with 400 professionals from more than 30 different nations, but also be part of a global organization allowing for collaboration with customers and colleagues across the world. Most importantly, you will be expected to make a difference. We are very proud of our culture of trust and helpfulness.
The position is a combined role as a Scrum Master & Functional tester in one of our test teams that support our developer teams with test activities.
Position Responsibilities:
Help the team to collaborate and perform at its best, by removing impediments and facilitating an open communication during Agile events
Facilitates the team’s progress toward team goals
Lead training workshops to educate key individuals on the pragmatics of Lean-Agile values, principles, and practices.
Coach continuous improvement of the way we work.
To work as a Systems Test Engineer means that you have to understand system behavior and performance.
Take test coach role together with other team members.
Perform system and integration testing as release moves through different environments before Production deployment
Contribute and support in testing activities.
Actively participate in our Scrum Master network and support your Scrum Masters colleagues
About the Carma Team
Today the Carma Team is comprised of 4 testers and a PO.
We are a DevOps Support Team with a responsibility of system testing, integration testing and release candidate testing.
We do have some responsibilities related to testing environment, and infrastructure.
For automation we use tools such UFT, Gherkin and bash scripts.
We do have a lot of collaboration with other feature teams and support them in testing areas.
Required Qualifications:
We believe you have an analytical approach to problem solving, good communication skills both within and outside your team and an interest in technology as well as human relations.
Fluency in English (our corporate language), spoken and written.
Any prior software development or testing experience (Frontend, Backend and platform applications)
Certified Scrum Master (CSM, SAFe) or equivalent professional qualification.
Understanding of the technical enablers of Agile delivery and how they operate within an Agile organization (e.g., CI, CD)
Knowledge and Experience of test automation for complex, distributed architecture but test automation with UFT and Gherkin is a bonus.
Have experience with tools like Gitlab, Unix/Linux, and Jira
Experience working in SAFe, Agile environment
Basic knowledge in cloud technologies, for example AWS services
Good to have experience and interest in DevSecOps
We also think you are driven, committed, have a positive attitude and are comfortable with continuous team growth and having fun.
Relocation:
This position does not offer relocation. Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense.

Title: Service Engineer - 409154
Description:
What if you could participate in the strategic decisions of a leading mobility company?

Leading societies to a low carbon future, Alstom develops and markets mobility solutions that provide the sustainable foundations for the future of transportation. Our product portfolio ranges from high-speed trains, metros, monorail, trams and e-buses to integrated systems, customised services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility solutions. Joining us means joining a caring, responsible, and innovative company where 75,000 people lead the way to greener and smarter mobility, worldwide.

Join us as a Service Engineer in Gothenburg, Sweden and you will be looking at a career-defining role.

Your mission?

As a Service Engineer, you will mainly be carrying out warranty measures on M33 trams at the depot Slottsskogen in southern Gothenburg. The tasks are varied and include warranty repairs, troubleshooting, modifications and commissioning of M33 trams. Shifts occur and you will work with competent and committed colleagues who will help you get into the work and the team in the best way. There are works in the customer's other depots (depot Rantorget & depot Majorna).

What your mission includes:
Perform troubleshooting and warranty repairs of M33 trams. Carry out testing and commissioning of vehicles according to instructions. Manage technical surveys. Handle reporting of field data as well as other administration of forms etc. Support maintenance documentation validation. Be up to date regarding changes in maintenance documentation.
Perform modifications according to instruction and drawing documentation in English.
In English , register completed warranty work and root cause analyses in our digital maintenance system Maximo

Your profile?

As a service engineer, it is of great importance that you are driven and have a solid technical interest and ability to solve complex problems. We are looking for you who have experience of technical work from the automation industry, aviation, trains or the like where repair & troubleshooting of mechanical, electrical and digital control systems belongs to your everyday life.

Minimum qualifications:
Graduate in Engineering with a minimum 5 years of technical experience, either mechanical or electrical / electronic engineering
EHS knowledge/exposure
Product knowledge
Data analytics
Fluent in English & Swedish

Ideally:
Railway knowledge
Field Experience
Problem Solving skills

Why Alstom?
Alstom is the leading company in the railway sector, solving the most interesting challenges for tomorrow’s mobility. That’s why we value inquisitive and innovative people who are passionate about working together to reinvent mobility, making it smarter and more sustainable. Day after day, we are building an agile, inclusive and responsible culture, where a diverse group of people are offered opportunities to learn, grow and advance in their careers, with options across functions and geographic locations. Are you ready to join a truly international community of great people on a challenging journey with a tangible impact and purpose?

Alstom is an equal opportunity employer committed to creating an inclusive working environment where all our employees are encouraged to reach their full potential, and individual differences are valued and respected. All qualified applicants are considered for employment without regard to race, colour, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, national origin, disability status, or any other characteristic protected by local law.

Title: Senior Group Internal Auditor 'Operations'
Description:
Change the way we work. Shape living for the better.
At Electrolux, a leading global appliance company, we strive every day to shape living for the better for our consumers, our people and our planet. We share ideas and collaborate so that together, we can develop solutions that deliver enjoyable and sustainable living.
Come join us as you are. We believe diverse perspectives make us stronger and more innovative. In our global community of people from 100+ countries, we listen to each other, actively contribute and grow together.
Join us in our exciting quest to build the future home.
All about the role:
Do you have an analytical mindset and is curiosity in your DNA? Do you understand Purchasing, Supply Chain or Manufacturing processes? And are you energized by travelling the world and meeting leaders and experts?
We are now looking for an internal auditor to join our Operations Internal Audit team. Your mission will be to help Electrolux achieve its strategic objectives by performing audits across the Group. You will partner with global leaders as well as the regional functions across the world. You will define key risks. You will conduct audits in an independent way, leveraging the best of people and technology.
You will be based at our headquarters in Stockholm, but your field of responsibility spans our worldwide operations, and you will be travelling frequently to Electrolux offices all around the world. You will report to the Internal Audit Manager CX & Operations.
What you'll do:
As part of a team of functional experts in Group Internal Audit, you will stay in tune with the latest developments both internally and externally. You will review risk areas for errors, waste and fraud within Operations processes. You will formulate audit work programs and lead assignments to evaluate processes, in order to give independent assurance and provide actionable insights for driving improvement. Part of your regular activities will also be to monitor data, identify risks and perform risk assessment activities to build the internal audit plan for the Operations area.
In detail, you will:
Lead and execute audit assignments that result in documented assurance about the integrity of our processes
Interface with leadership across Electrolux to present the audit plan, discuss findings and insights, and review progress of open issues
Participate in the risk assessment activities to identify what should be audited and how, through interviews, data analysis and audit history
Perform periodic testing to assess the operating effectiveness of internal controls
Drive projects to improve the internal audit process
Qualifications:
Academic degree (preferably in business, economics or similar)
3 years of relevant work experience (primarily in purchasing, manufacturing, finance or audit)
Data analytics skills (experience in tools such as Qlik, PowerBI or Tableau)
Fluent in English (additional languages are a strong plus)
Ability to travel
Where you'll be:
You will be based at our Global headquarters on Kungsholmen in Stockholm, Sweden.
Benefits highlights:
Flexible work hours/hybrid work environment
Discounts on our award-winning Electrolux products and services
Family and health friendly benefits
Generous vacation
Extensive learning opportunities and flexible career path
As part of Electrolux, we will continuously invest in you and your development. There are no barriers to where your career could take you.
Find out more:
Electrolux Group

Title: Failure Analysis Engineer
Description:
We are looking for a driven Failure Analysis Engineer to join us in our mission to contribute to a greener future. The role is a part of our passionate Quality Control team based in Västerås, Sweden. By joining us, you will be a key player and have an active role in battery cell investigations, develop key failure analysis competences and contribute towards building one of the first large scale European battery factories.
About the job
As Failure Analysis Engineer, you will engage in (participate or lead) cell failure analyses and hands-on investigation activities related to battery cell production and test performance. The investigations you will be involved in could cover a broad range of issues, including cell chemistry, manufacturing variability, mechanical performance, contaminant identification, and analysis of test and field failures. In this role, we expect you to have a Gemba mindset and a hands-on approach to your tasks. You enjoy working in the laboratory and on the factory floor, as well as can effectively collaborate across group boundaries to pull in technical input and resources as required to find answers and solutions to problems.
About the team
Together with two further engineers you will be part of the Failure Analysis team within our wider Quality Control team at Northvolt Labs. Our QC team, currently composed of 25 dedicated laboratory technicians, analytical chemists and engineers, is working on all aspects of cell production investigations and quality inspections. You will have access to a fully equipped laboratory with high-end analytical instruments that cover both chemical and mechanical analyses. You will play a key role in building up cell failure analysis expertise within the team and the wider company.
Key responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Rapid response (hours, not days) to and investigation of various new or unsolved defect types in battery cells and components
Using standard methodologies or non-standard techniques (as appropriate), investigate issues and concerns within cells from hands-on manual cell disassembly’s to analyzing components and parts with analytical methods/techniques available in the laboratory
Trigger and drive the exchange of technical expertise across departments depending on the matter of interest to achieve data driven, scientific results as input for root cause investigations. You do not have to be an expert in everything, but you do need to be an expert in identifying the subject matter, finding the specific expert(s) for that field, and finding answers
Data driven approach with an analytical mindset, ability to deal with different levels of complexity (obvious cases vs. deep dives). Insist on answers and solutions that can be substantiated by data and/or engineering tests, avoiding the trap of finding a root cause driven by timelines instead of science
Strive to bring in more cell-inexperienced personnel occasionally during hands-on investigations to increase the overall cell knowledge within Northvolt. You should bring good people skills to the job, and are eager to learn and train others
Every FA engineer brings a unique skillset and knowledge base to the game, but all members must hone skill with at least all of the following equipment, techniques, and test methods: optical microscopy, photo-documentation and report generation, manual disassembly and manipulation using pipe cutters/cell cutters/manual disassembly tools/picks/probes, multimeters, Dremel tool, soldering iron, hipot testing, and use of the Hioki-brand electrical test systems.

Personal success factors:
Promoting and requiring facts and data to drive decision making in the organisation
Strong communication skills with all the key stakeholders and experts in a wide variety of technical disciplines
Proactive, strong-minded, quick thinker and assertive
Passionate and purpose driven
Has a can-do attitude and an entrepreneurial spirit
When the answer is No, figures out how to get to Yes
Northvolt is an equal opportunity employer.
