Title: Digital Product Designer
Description:
Are you ready to redefine the financial industry? Are you looking to leave an impact on the financial lives, and futures, of hundreds of thousands of families across the Nordics? Are you driven by designing the products of the future and simplifying a slow-moving industry in a fast-moving fintech company?
Then Nordnet is the place for you! We are looking for talented Digital Product Designer who want to create world-class user experiences and redefine the financial industry.
As a Digital Product Designer
You'll be a part of our Award winning Design team which you will closely collaborate with during our journey of creating Nordnet Design System and one unified design experience. We see you as a key contributor in delivering high quality human-centered solutions your primary focus will be on delivering great variety of delightful designs for Nordnet CMS pages.
On daily basis you’ll be working with cross-functional teams and different stakeholders (bringing together design, agile, engineering, business, data analytics, product and domain owners, etc.) hand in hand when delivering designs. You will also tackle all aspects of the design and business building process, often through leading interactive workshops and design sprints to foster innovation, collaboration, and alignment between Product design & Marketing teams.

This is part of the role
Maintaining a close collaboration with the Marketing team and copywriters to work together on content personalisation.
Leveraging all your design capabilities to prototype and iterate on UX/UI design including sketching, information architecture, wireframes and user flows.
Supporting and when necessary conducting usability testing sessions, synthesising findings and iteratively
integrating them into design solutions.
You'll think both creatively and strategically, supporting dissecting business problems by using different design methodologies to develop innovative outcomes that communicate the product vision.
Innovating and helping Nordnet Brand and Design System grow by creating and maintaining CMS Design component libraries.
Maintaining a close collaboration with development teams to handle design handoff and design QA sessions.
Creating interactive presentations and showcase your work towards business and various stakeholders.
This is you
You are a passionate designer with a proven track record of great designs and strategy that meet end-user needs, product requirements and business objectives.
You have a relevant industry experience designing digital experiences, websites, applications, products and services that balance user needs, business objectives and technological constraints.
You have an eye for detail and an excellent sense of aesthetics and functionality and are able to create in a rapid iterative design process.
You are familiar with tools such as Figma, FigJam, Miro, Adobe Creative Suite, Framer or other motion software, etc.
You are familiar with the Agile software development process and tools such as Jira and Confluence.
You have experience in building Design System and maintaining design system libraries.
You embrace innovation and enjoy collaborating with the team to ensure Design System growth.
You can animate complex design interactions if necessary to support communication with development team to ensure the expected design quality.
You have excellent professional language skills in English, both verbally and in writing.
As a person you are experimental and self-driven while also being collaborative. We are looking for a problem solver with great communication skills and a positive attitude. It is important for us to work in an organized way and that you are able to self manage through your design sprints and drive design work, workshops and presentations with great time management. You are passionate and enjoy driving your own work forward and can collaborate and present your ideas to different stakeholders in the organization.
Hey, we are a bank so it is a plus if you have experience within a Fintech sector!
This is us
We are currently building a world-class customer experience and have a vision to become the number one choice for savings and investments in the Nordic countries. Our ambitions are high and you will embark on a fast and challenging journey within a tight team of sharp and committed colleagues. At Nordnet, there is great potential for development and opportunities to redefine the financial world.
We are 800 employees in Stockholm, Oslo, Helsinki and Copenhagen.
Learn more about Nordnet on our corporate site and in our brand movie This is Nordnet, that describes our identity.
You can also visit us on www.nordnet.se, www.nordnet.no, www.nordnet.dk and www.nordnet.fi
Questions & Application
If you have questions, please contact Talent Acquisition Partner Alva Hellberg at alva.hellberg@nordnet.se
Apply today by using the button below – we will start interviewing immediately.
Please note that we do only accept applications through our recruitment system, hence no email applications will be considered.
We want to inform you that Nordnet conduct credit and background checks on the final candidate.
We look forward to receiving your application!

Title: Sökes; Sveriges trevligaste BI-utvecklare
Description:
Placering Malmö, Helsingborg, Halmstad, Göteborg, Växjö, Stockholm
Erfarenhet Medior, Senior
Omfattning Fulltime

Snabbfakta

Område: Data & AI
Start: Omgående
Omfattning: Heltid
Placering: Malmö, Helsingborg, Halmstad eller Göteborg

Eventuella frågor och funderingar tas med Anders Larsson som du når på 0736-448550.

Hos Fellowmind är området Business Intelligence & Data Analytics under stark tillväxt och vi söker dig som vill vara med på den resan. Är du en person som kan omvandla data till affärsmöjligheter? Har du ett brinnande intresse för att hitta nya och bättre lösningar? Är AI och Machine Learning kanske någonting du redan jobbat med eller är intresserad av? Perfekt, då är du den vi söker!

För oss på Fellowmind handlar teknik om att skapa kontakter. Och där tekniken kopplar oss samman är det vi människor som skapar mening. Vi sätter alltid våra medarbetare i första rummet – det har tagit oss dit vi är idag! Klicka här om du vill veta mer om oss.

Om tjänsten

Vi på Fellowmind är en helhetsleverantör inom Business Intelligence och Data Analytics. På det stora hela kommer du, tillsammans med våra kunder, att bygga lösningar som hjälper organisationen att bättre se, förstå och agera utifrån sin data. Du kommer att få arbeta med både skräddarsydda och paketerade lösningar inom beslutsstöd, utifrån beprövade koncept. Datakällorna är alla möjliga (och omöjliga) men det är också det som sporrar oss, att hela tiden hitta nya vägar framåt till grymma lösningar för våra kunder!

Din förmåga att applicera dina kunskaper till kunders verksamhet blir helt avgörande för att göra ändringar i befintliga delar eller skapa helt nya funktioner för våra kunder. Som BI-utvecklare hos oss jobbar du alltid nära kundernas kravställare och användare viket gör att du själv får se nyttan som dina lösningar skapar. Du kommer bli delaktig i ett tidigt skede av projekten vara delaktig i hela processen från ax till limpa;

Kravhantering av affärslogik
Översätta kravhantering till teknisk specifikation
Utveckling och programmering av både kundunika lösningar och paketeringar och koncept
Förvaltning av både våra paketeringar och koncept samt kundernas lösningar

Teknisk innebär det att du bl.a. kommer att jobba med;

The modern Datawarehouse – Azure Data Factory/Data Lake/Analyses Services/SQL mfl
The traditional Datawarehouse - SQL Server (inkl. SSIS/SSAS/SSRS)
Microsoft Power BI
Machine Learning/AI

Ofta kommer du vara en del av större projekt som involverar flera delar på Microsoftplattformen som exempelvis ERP, CRM, Modern Work (Microsoft 365/SharePoint) där du står för expertisen inom BI.

Vem är du?

Vi söker dig som är senior inom Business Intelligence med minst 3 års erfarenhet och som vill vara med på vår resa. Troligtvis jobbar du idag som konsult eller sitter på det som vi kallar kundsidan, men då inte enbart som användare utan snarare utvecklare/förvaltare inom BI. Har du dessutom erfarenhet inom ERP, och mer specifikt Dynamics (FO/AX eller NAV/BC) är det mycket meriterande.

Givetvis är det meriterande om du har en bakgrund inom Microsoft-stacken (och delar av ovan nämnda teknikbitar) men du kan även ha en bakgrund inom exempelvis Qlik, Tableau eller Hypergene. I grunden tror vi att du har någon slags högskoleutbildning inom exempelvis datateknik, systemvetenskap eller motsvarande.

Som person är du nyfiken, vill framåt och håller dig ajour inom ditt område. Då projekten kan innefatta alltifrån självständigt arbete till att bli en del av ett projektteam är det viktigt att du är van att arbeta självständigt samtidigt som du trivs med att samarbeta. Du har en god analytisk förmåga, är detaljorienterad och gillar att jobba med problemlösning. Vi ser också̊ att du har förmågan att snabbt sätta dig in i nya arbetsprocesser och system. Och givetvis som vi skriver i titeln så är du trevlig!

Eftersom du hjälper våra kunder utefter deras behov söker vi dig som har obehindrade språkkunskaper i såväl svenska som engelska, i både skrift och tal.

Vill du bli en del av oss?

Vill du veta mer om vilka karriärmöjligheter det finns hos oss på Fellowmind? Philip Arcangioli är Talent Acquisition Specialist hos oss och hjälper dig gärna med alla dina frågor!

Mejla Philip!

Title: Software Engineer, Commercial Systems
Description:
This engineering role is an opportunity for a technologist with a passion for Linux to build a career with Canonical and drive the success of those leveraging Ubuntu and open source products. If you have an affinity for open source development, you will enjoy working with some of the best people in the industry at Canonical.
The Commercial Systems unit has several areas of responsibility spread across five engineering teams, closely collaborating with other engineering and business teams at Canonical. Services designed, developed, and operated by the Commercial Systems unit are deployed to millions of machines worldwide.
The first area of responsibility is centered around security. We develop and operate Ubuntu Pro and Livepatch backend services that support the authentication, authorization, and delivery of Extended Security Maintenance (ESM) at scale to a wide range of devices spanning from individual systems to large enterprise fleets running in cloud environments.
On the distributed systems front, we develop an open source identity manager Candid and a Juju multi-controller manager JIMM (Juju Intelligent Model Manager), that enables organizations to centrally manage operations across many Juju controllers deployed to public, private, and hybrid clouds. The majority of our systems are deployed to Kubernetes clusters.
The third major area is related to internal business operations. We develop and operate a data warehouse, including data ingestion pipelines, that are relied on by operations and data analytics teams. In addition to that, we help internal business units to automate processes across many software solutions and integrate SaaS solutions to ensure a smooth flow of data.
Lastly, we have a dedicated team of Salesforce engineers and administrators who take care of our Salesforce implementation and integration crucial to our sales and business operations. This team configures Salesforce and implements business processes that facilitate efficient operations.
We are looking for new colleagues with strong background in Go or Python, who have the drive and energy to deliver and operate solutions at scale with the highest engineering quality, continuously develop their skills, and work with us on defining the future of open source.
We expect you to have
Bachelor's degree or equivalent in Computer Science or related engineering field.
Experience as a software developer in a high-level language - preferably Go or Python.
Experience building, deploying, and operating distributed systems and APIs.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English.
Ability to collaborate remotely with a diverse set of team members and stakeholders, remain highly motivated, productive, and organized in a fully remote environment.
Ability to travel to international destinations for one week at a time, approximately 2-4 times per year. Locations prior to the global pandemic included New York, Seattle, London, Cape Town, Budapest, Berlin, Montreal, and Brussels.
Nice to have
Experience developing and deploying for Ubuntu Linux in public clouds.
Experience integrating authentication & authorization, financial, public cloud or marketplace systems.
Experience with Salesforce development/integration or APEX.
We offer
Learning and Development opportunities and budget
Annual compensation review
Recognition rewards
Annual leave
Priority pass for travel
Flexible working option
Canonical believes a diverse workforce enhances our ability to deliver world class software and services which meet the world's computing needs. We are committed to ensuring equal employment opportunities to all qualified individuals. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status.

Title: Product Marketing Lead
Description:
Jeppesen, a subsidiary of The Boeing Company, is one of the largest software development companies in Gothenburg. We develop innovative optimization solutions for the world’s leading airlines. We are dedicated to continuous improvement, delivering more value to our clients, and exploring emerging technologies such as quantum computing, AI and Big Data analytics.
At our central Gothenburg office, we are currently looking for a Product Marketing Lead to work with our portfolio of Crew and Network Operations products.
Product Marketing Assignment
At Jeppesen in Gothenburg, we are developing and promoting applications used for Airline Crew, Network and Operations Management, which are used in the airline Operation Control Center (OCC). Crew Product Portfolio – we provide airlines with solutions that help airlines improve operational stability, maximize schedule safety, and even create opportunities to improve crew quality of life.
Network & Operations Management Portfolio – we provide airlines with solutions that help with assigning the right aircraft to the right flight to predict and prevent down-line disruptions, these tools assist to lighten the airline staff’s workload, so teams can focus more time on strategic, value-adding activities.

Position Responsibilities:
The Product Marketing Lead will work directly with Portfolio teams, Marketing, Sales, and Product Development to oversee and provide guidance on communicating technical aspects, value and benefits of Boeing/Jeppesen products to airline customers, media, internal partners, and other key constituencies.
Leads the development of product and service messaging to promote the value of products and services and differentiate them from the competition.
Consults and provides guidance on Boeing and competitors’ products and services to internal customers to support business decisions, sales strategies and training etc. Providing market guidance for annual long-range business planning.
Communicates discovered customer feedback and requested requirements to influence the development of new or improved products, services and features. In addition, the PMM works to provide input and guidance on technical and business benefits, advantages and differentiators of products and services supporting the strategic positioning of Boeing/Jeppesen products and services.
Serves as key member of multiple cross functional teams.

Required Qualifications
Fluent in English
Bachelor’s Degree or Master’s Degree from an accredited course of study or equivalent
Natural customer and partner relationship building skills: Develops and sustains productive customer and partner relationships.
Product, Operational and Acquisition Process Acumen: Confidently and effectively integrates product, operational knowledge and acquisition process into a customer discussion.
Customer Knowledge: Knowledge of techniques to help identify a customer's organization, capabilities, practices, support resources, preferences, problems, and other constraints in order to provide effective product support and technical issue resolution.
Marketing Analytical Methods: Knowledge of marketing core analytical methods and tools (e.g., Operating Cost, Performance, Fleet Planning, Network Analysis, Financial, Revenue Analysis, etc).
Marketing Materials and Media: Demonstrates an expert understanding of using integrated marketing and media strategies. Ability to write creative briefs that clearly articulate creative direction and measures of success in order to inform internal and external resources. Be able to develop product messaging that articulates value creation and benefits.
Presentation Skills and Techniques: Knowledge of presentation techniques.
Drive to understand customers’ needs and priorities: Places priority on understanding customer needs and takes ownership on finding solutions, effectively using empathy, and patience and collaboration skills.
Influence the customer and shape requirements: Uses appropriate techniques in order to gain agreement and commitment to drive results.

Preferred Qualifications
Airline Industry Knowledge: Have a working knowledge of the typical airline organization, operations, policies and procedures, products, requirements, capabilities, practices, constraints, etc. as it relates to flight operations.
Industry Awareness: Understands, builds, and uses industry knowledge for planning and performance accomplishment. This includes knowledge of competition and strategic partners.
Product and Services Value: Knowledge of the value that Boeing/Jeppesen products and services bring to customer airline's business (cost and revenue implications) from both an internal and customer perspective. Understands value analysis methodologies used by multiple airline customers to effectively demonstrate Boeing/Jeppesen product and services advantages to drive customer perceptions, airplane and service purchase decisions, and influence business decisions.

Typical Education/Experience:
Education/experience typically acquired through advanced technical education (e.g. Bachelor) and typically 14 or more years' related work experience or an equivalent combination of technical education and experience (e.g. PhD+9 years' related work experience, Master+12 years' related work experience, 18 years' related work experience, etc.).
More questions?
Further information of our portfolio is found at https://ww2.jeppesen.com/airline-crew-optimization-solutions/
Employer is willing to sponsor applicants for employment visa status.
Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense. This requisition is for an international, locally hired position in Sweden. Successful candidates must be able to obtain and maintain legal authorization to work in Sweden for continued employment. Benefits and pay are determined at the local level and are not part of Boeing U.S. based payroll.
Relocation: This position does not offer relocation. Candidates must live in the immediate area or relocate at their own expense.

Title: VIE Business Analyst ComplyLog
Description:
Euronext is the leading pan-European exchange in the Eurozone with nearly 2,000 listed issuers worth close to €6.9 trillion in market capitalisation (as of end 2020). Euronext operates the regulated equity and derivatives markets of Paris, Amsterdam, Oslo, Dublin, Brussels, Lisbon, and has recently acquired Borsa Italiana.
As part of its strategic plan, Euronext has engaged into the development of a complete service offering to listed and non-listed companies. Euronext Corporate Services ("Corporate Services") offers innovative solutions and tailor-made advisory services to support organisations to run more efficiently.
The Corporate Services team is composed of over 120 enthusiastic professionals that combine a strong local footprint across Europe with a deep understanding of global capital markets. They help organisations, both listed and non-listed, private and public, make the most effective use of capital markets and run more efficiently.
This unique and comprehensive value proposition is articulated around four main pillars:

Governance : Our board portal solution, iBabs helps organizations to secure, organize and run board meetings more efficiently (save time preparing agendas and board packs, collaborate easily with annotations, voting, meeting summaries).

Communication : Company Webcast is the market leader in webinars and webcasts services for financial results, internal communication, marketing and external communication. With Company Webcast, we help our clients to increase their visibility, engagement and international coverage. We also provide flexible and customized market data components for Investor Relations websites of listed companies.

Compliance : ComplyLog is a range of groundbreaking digital tools, designed by legal experts to help companies more easily meet the growing demands of European compliance laws and corporate regulations.

Investor Relations : Our Advisory team provides high-touch advisory, market intelligence, shareholder analysis, targeting, and decision making analytics for listed companies willing to be more active on capital markets. Our IR.Manager tool provides a complete and intuitive IR management and targeting platform for corporate IR teams to professionalize the workflow and engagement.

Read more at
https://corporateservices.euronext.com/
Key Accountabilities:
The analyst will support the
ComplyLog
business in a wide variety of missions, mainly covering sales, marketing and operational developments taking part in high impact projects for the division.
He/she will be working in close collaboration with ComplyLog management team reporting directly to the Managing Director.
Key Accountabilities:
Support the execution of high-impact, cross-functional projects
Contribute to the strategic planning and structuring of the ComplyLog business
Conduct market research and competitive analysis for all our products and geographies
Create workflow management and tools to accelerate the performance of the business
Assist in punctual sales and marketing origination efforts, including the set-up of prospection campaigns or in the follow-up of commercial opportunities
Be on top of the latest industry trends and technology disruptions

This role is part of the V.I.E international graduate programme which only accepts candidates with a European Union citizenship and with a current residency outside of Sweden, willing to relocate to Stockholm
Master's Degree in Finance, or engineering school
Command of Excel & Powerpoint

Title: Product Introduction Manager Nordics
Description:
Leading societies to a low carbon future, Alstom develops and markets mobility solutions that provide the sustainable foundations for the future of transportation. Our product portfolio ranges from high-speed trains, metros, monorail, and trams to integrated systems, customised services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility solutions. Joining us means joining a caring, responsible, and innovative company where more than 70,000 people lead the way to greener and smarter mobility, worldwide

JOIN US AS A PRODUCT INTRODUCTION MANAGER NORDICS!

Purpose of the job

Manage the overall Product Introduction (PI) activities on a site, in a country, in a cluster, a region or platform such as validation support, commissioning & warranty with the objective to minimize and to improve project PI cost base, notably PI non-core costs.
Is accountable for PI strategic development within his business perimeter including up-sell identification

Key accountabilities:

Manage all PI activities & resources (commissioning, validation support and warranty) for all projects in its region/cluster/country/site or platform.
Manage tenders/bids related to PI scope (for all allocated projects whether origin or destination)
Manage and approve Quality Cost Delivery (QCD) budget commitment for PI scope for the site/country/cluster/region/platform at tender and execution phase
Lead the initiative for PI cost optimization & recovery of non-core costs through continuous improvement
Ensure adequate supplier warranty duration and recovery of charge-back
Ensure proper management of Reliability Growth, availability and other contractual commitments with respect to product warranty
Manage critical interface with Customer representatives (support Project Product Introduction Manager (PrPIM))
Ensure proper implementation and respect of Environment Health & Safety (EHS) and Railways Safety
Ensure people recruitment and competency development according to needs of all relevant PI activities
Ensure proper PI Return of Experience to other operational functions (Engineering, Industrial, Testing, Quality, ...)
Ensure PI standard process deployment and adherence including audit/assessment performance (internal and external)
Ensure an optimization of PI execution in collaboration with Services organization, if applicable (Operation / Maintenance contracts)
Support PrPIM in driving other Functions' contribution to the achievement of PI commitments and targets
Promote the Alstom Code of Ethics and adherence to the highest standards of ethical conduct
Ensure consistency of PI execution and operation amongst tenders & projects and different product lines
Manage interface with Customer Directors, Project Directors, Service Director, and Head of operational functions such as Quality and Engineering
Support PI set-up during Transfer of Technology, if applicable
Accountable for PI Key Performance Indicator (KPI)'s deployment and proper reporting & analysis (finance, technical, cost & non-cost related, …)

Your profile
Graduate in Engineering or Industrial
Senior experience in Project execution
Global and Team management
EHS knowledge/exposure
Railway Safety/Product liability
Product knowledge
Data analytics

Alstom is the leading company in the mobility sector, solving the most interesting challenges for tomorrow’s mobility. That’s why we value inquisitive and innovative people who are passionate about working together to reinvent mobility, making it smarter and more sustainable. Day after day, we are building an agile, inclusive and responsible culture, where a diverse group of people are offered opportunities to learn, grow and advance in their careers, with options across functions and geographic locations. Are you ready to join a truly international community of great people on a challenging journey with a tangible impact and purpose?

Title: (Senior) Product Owner/Manager - Information Retrieval Platform
Description:
Applications are considered on a rolling basis Gothenburg

We are looking for a passionate and seasoned Product Owner to join our Product Management organization and lead our information retrieval platform development.

At Meltwater, we are creating the next generation media intelligence solutions for a global client base. In support of this vision, the information retrieval team operates and evolves the most central part of Meltwater’s vast library of content, playing a key role in the storage and access of all of the company’s current editorial, social, and broadcast media assets by building a platform that provides petabyte-scale search and analytics capabilities.

This mission is central to Meltwater’s growth, highly visible to executives, and plays a strategic role in our Enterprise offerings. As Product Owner/Manager for this team, you will work directly with sales, customers, and other product owners to drive product delivery and inspire the team to build the best products possible. You will have a direct impact on product direction, positioning, and, ultimately our business strategy.

If you are intrigued by the opportunity of helping companies around the globe improve communication with their employees by extracting business-critical insights from millions of online conversations and engaging their employees in relevant news, you should continue reading.

What you'll do

Confidently articulate and evolve the vision for the information retrieval platform.

Work closely with stakeholders across the organization to ensure that you and the team provide for the company’s short- and long-term goals.

Helps the team realize the value of their work and appreciate how their deliverables impact the business.

Define, track, and interpret critical metrics to ensure your team is doing the right things while not spreading out too thin. A healthy balance of innovation, support, and maintenance is key for all successful teams at Meltwater.

Manage your own and the team’s availability - given stakeholders across the globe, we sometimes need to join/host meetings outside typical office hours.

Represent your product both internally and externally. Acting as a key evangelist and product expert.

The position is offered in our office in Gothenburg, Sweden. We are remote-friendly but expect you to come to the office from time to time to work with your colleagues in person.

SKILLS & REQUIREMENTS

Who you are

You have at least 3+ years of experience managing and developing software products as a PM/PO in an agile product development environment.

You have experience working in a B2B SaaS or platform business environment.

You are an interdisciplinary thinker, skilled at blending different perspectives in pursuing a mission.

You have a proven ability to understand complex business problems, apply strong analytical skills, and create an effective strategy.

You have a proven track record of delivering technical solutions for large-scale business problems.

You have excellent written and verbal communication skills; you can effectively communicate at varying levels of technical detail with all levels and types of internal stakeholders in one-on-one and group situations.

You have excellent leadership and relationship-building skills.

You are good at sorting out ambiguity.

You are fluent in English.

Bonus Skills

Scrum Product Owner certification (CSPO).

Experience with data mining, search engines, and big data analytics.

Experience defining products & solutions containing large data sets from multiple sources.

Background in Big Data, specifically around volume, velocity, and veracity.

Professional background includes software development.

GREAT PLACE TO WORK

Competitive Salary

Fresh fruits & free drinks

Internal hackathons

Personal Branding Support

Ergonomic desks and chairs

Great hardware

Opportunities to travel in Europe and the U.S.

Open Source Contributions

Conferences and Tech Talks

ABOUT THE COMPANY

Meltwater, a pioneer of media intelligence and now Outside Insight, gives businesses the information advantage they need to stay ahead. More than 30,000 companies have used Meltwater’s media intelligence to stay on top of billions of online conversations and extract relevant insights to strategically manage their brands. Meltwater is dedicated to personal, global service built on the local expertise of 55 offices across six continents. Meltwater is also committed to fostering the data science ecosystem through MEST, a pan-African entrepreneurial program and incubator, and Shack15, a global data science community. Learn more at meltwater.com.

All of our solutions are fully web-based, offered as a service, and based on a modern technology stack. This is your opportunity to be part of a small agile team within a big multinational organization!

We are more than 2000 people across the globe, so there is a lot going on. We believe in diversity and inclusion, and building teams with a wide variety of backgrounds and perspectives. This approach not only raises the quality of our products for our customers, but makes collaboration along the way much more fun.

Read our underthehood blog to see which problems our engineers are solving. Also have a look at what life is like at Meltwater and visit our company profiles on LinkedIn, Xing, Facebook, and Twitter.

Equal Opportunity

Meltwater is firmly committed to affording equal employment opportunities to all candidates and employees alike without regard to race, color, religion, age, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or gender expression, marital status disability, veteran status and we treat each individual with respect and dignity.

Title: Chief System Architect
Description:
With 950 employees, over $250M in sales, 1,500+ clients, and rapid year-over-year growth, Recorded Future is the world's most advanced, and largest, intelligence company!
The Chief System Architect is a senior role in the Recorded Future product organisation. We are looking for someone with a minimum of 15 years experience. We are looking at someone with at least a Master's degree in the technology field from a top university. Must understand and be hands-on in Software Development and Big Data analytics. Must have an excellent professional demeanour and the ability to effectively conduct technical presentations for clients/potential clients, other technology partners and stakeholders as well as internal developers, executives etc. Must be able to travel globally to manage our large product with development in 4 main hubs in Europe, USA and Asia.
The primary roles of the Chief System Architect is to provide hands-on architecture leadership, guidance and mentoring to our distributed engineering teams, be a close collaborator and trusted advisor to the Chief of R&D and the CTO, and ensure the delivery of high-quality, robust, and scalable solutions.
What you'll do as a Chief System Architect:

The Chief System Architect is a key leadership role, responsible for driving and developing new and creative innovative approaches, which will serve as the basis for the company's next generation technology; help to develop the vision, definition, and strategy for the software engineering team by driving project/program initiatives that deliver on the company's vision and strategy. In addition, the Chief System Architect is tasked with working with the team in solving technical issues on performance, scalability, and enterprise systems including over technical leadership for the full product life cycle i.e., requirements gathering, design, development, testing and deployment.
Specific Responsibilities & Objectives:
Provide architectural and technical guidance to the engineering organisations.
Deliver quality software releases with focus on quality and time.
Strong experience with SaaS solutions
Be responsible for architectural development to achieve corporate goals and clients' requirements.
Do requirements analysis, system/software design and analysis, development/software metric creation and analysis, system risk analysis, integration, and test metrics.
Develop, present and maintain a strategic architecture roadmap in close relation with the product leadership team.
Translate product requirements into engineering specifications
Provide leadership to the software engineering team and enforce architectural baselines
Anticipate future system needs and be proactive in identifying solutions from a scaling and performance perspective
Evaluate and identify new technologies for implementation
Support, maintain, and document our architecture
Lead architectural aspects of incorporating acquired companies' systems into Recorded Future.
Architectural documentation
Coaching of others
What you'll bring as a Chief System Architect:
At least a Master's degree in Computer Science or similar from a top university.
Extensive 10+ years experience with developing and delivering commercial enterprise software
At least 5 years Experience in software architecture and engineering
Extensive experience with distributed systems, cloud computing, CI/CD
Experience with Java/Scala and a good understanding of React or similar is a plus
Prior experience in developing profiling tools, big data analytics and rules-based systems through the application of fuzzy logic and machine learning
Personal Characteristics:

He/she will exhibit the personal drive, passion, innovative thinking and enthusiasm to both understand and successfully navigate a fast-growing company striving towards maintaining market leadership in an evolving industry environment.
Strong leadership and people management skills with the ability to mentor a world-class engineering team and inspire strong workforce performance.
Strong character under pressure with excellent work ethic and professionalism
Effective communicator with excellent written and verbal communication skills; good listener with strong interpersonal skills.
Strong presentation skills, with demonstrated ability, experience, and presence to credibly engage a wide range of stakeholders, including clients and potential clients.
Confidence and can-do attitude with the ability to act quickly and decisively.
Pragmatic with a realistic sense of what is achievable given constraints.
Proactive, moving beyond his/her comfort zone in pursuit of the company's mission and vision.
Combination of personality traits, including collaboration and team work, honesty, integrity, intensity, and passion necessary to blend with the rest of the executive product team.
Availability for frequent, global travel

Title: Business Intelligence Developer to Telenor!
Description:
Who we are

At Telenor, we’re here to connect you to what matters most, and by doing so, empowering societies. As an employee, you will be part of a large, international organization that goes beyond customers – we want to play an important role in the societies we serve. Being connected can change your life, and we’re serious about helping our services make the widest possible impact.
Telenor is ongoing a strong digital transformation, rapidly heading towards a fully data driven future and hence investing in the field of Analytics. Come join us now

Title: Senior Salesforce Engineer, Commercial Systems
Description:
This engineering role is an opportunity for a technologist with a passion for Linux to build a career with Canonical and drive the success of those leveraging Ubuntu and open source products. If you have an affinity for open source development, you will enjoy working with some of the best people in the industry at Canonical.
The Commercial Systems unit has several areas of responsibility spread across five engineering teams, closely collaborating with other engineering and business teams at Canonical. Services designed, developed, and operated by the Commercial Systems unit are deployed to millions of machines worldwide.
The first area of responsibility is centered around security. We develop and operate Ubuntu Pro and Livepatch backend services that support the authentication, authorization, and delivery of Extended Security Maintenance (ESM) at scale to a wide range of devices spanning from individual systems to large enterprise fleets running in cloud environments.
On the distributed systems front, we develop an open source identity manager Candid and a Juju multi-controller manager JIMM (Juju Intelligent Model Manager), that enables organizations to centrally manage operations across many Juju controllers deployed to public, private, and hybrid clouds. The majority of our systems are deployed to Kubernetes clusters.
The third major area is related to internal business operations. We develop and operate a data warehouse, including data ingestion pipelines, that are relied on by operations and data analytics teams. In addition to that, we help internal business units to automate processes across many software solutions and integrate SaaS solutions to ensure a smooth flow of data.
Lastly, we have a dedicated team of Salesforce engineers and administrators who take care of our Salesforce implementation and integration crucial to our sales and business operations. This team configures Salesforce and implements business processes that facilitate efficient operations.
We are looking for a senior-level Salesforce engineer with a passion for engineering excellence and strong communication skills to tirelessly seek improvements, provide subject matter expertise, ensure a great user experience, and work with us to define the future of open source.
We expect you to have
Bachelor's degree or equivalent in Computer Science or a related engineering field.
Senior-level experience as a software developer on Salesforce.
Experience integrating Salesforce with other systems.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English.
Ability to collaborate remotely with diverse team members and stakeholders and remain highly motivated, productive, and organized in a fully remote environment.
Ability to travel to international destinations for one week at a time, approximately 2-4 times per year. Locations prior to the global pandemic included New York, Seattle, London, Cape Town, Budapest, Berlin, Montreal, and Brussels.
Nice to have
Experience as a software developer in a high-level language - preferably Go or Python.
Experience in a business role such as sales, finance, or operations.
We offer
Learning and development opportunities and personal budget
Annual compensation review
Recognition rewards
Annual leave
Priority pass for travel
We are proud to foster a workplace free of discrimination. Diversity of experience, perspectives, and background create a better work environment and better products. Whatever your identity we will give your application fair consideration.

Title: Salesforce Engineering Manager, Commercial Systems
Description:
This engineering management role is an opportunity for a technologist with a passion for Linux and Ubuntu to build a career with Canonical and drive the success of the business. If you have an affinity for open source development, then you will enjoy working with some of the best people in the industry at Canonical.
Our new Commercial Systems unit is conceived as five engineering teams that closely collaborate with other engineering and business teams at Canonical. Services designed, developed, and operated by the Commercial Systems unit are used by millions of machines all over the world. Apply here if you would like to run one of these teams. They cover the following areas:
A contracts service. We develop and operate a contracts service that, among others, supports the authentication, authorization, and delivery of Extended Security Maintenance (ESM) at scale to a wide range of devices spanning from individual systems to large enterprise fleets running in cloud environments via Ubuntu Advantage. This service also delivers certain contract-based services, like our kernel live patches.
JAAS/Identity/LivePatch. We take the operational scalability of Juju, Canonical's solution to public, private, and hybrid-cloud application management and orchestration, to the next level by developing JIMM (Juju Intelligent Model Manager) and Candid (open source identity manager) that enable organizations to operate clusters of Juju-enabled clouds at a scale. In addition to that, we deliver the LivePatch client package and the LivePatch server backend that integrate with the contracts service to deliver live patches for the Linux kernel.
Data lake and SAAS integration. The third major area is related to internal business operations. We develop and operate several data warehouses, including data ingestion pipelines, used by operations and data analytics teams. In addition to that, we help internal business units to automate processes across a number of software solutions and integrate with a number of SaaS solutions to ensure a smooth flow of data.
Integration with public clouds. The fourth major area or responsibility lies in integrating the contracts service with public clouds, such as Azure, AWS, and GCP, to deliver customers a seamless SAAS experience at the OS level, including access to Extended Security Maintenance and support offerings provided by Canonical personnel.
Salesforce. The fifth major area is centered around Salesforce. Our team of Salesforce engineers and administrators ensures that business operations teams have the right data at a hand and the right business processes in place. The team works closely with the four engineering teams and provides subject matter expertise.
We are looking for software engineering managers, ideally with strong background in Salesforce, who have the drive and energy to lead a team of engineers in delivering and operating these capabilities at scale, ensure the highest engineering quality, sharpen team skills, and work with us to define the future of open source.
We expect you to have
Bachelor's degree or equivalent in Computer Science or a related engineering field.
Experience with Salesforce development/integration or APEX.
Experience as a hands-on engineering manager or a team lead.
Experience building, deploying, and operating distributed systems and APIs.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English.
Ability to collaborate remotely with a diverse set of team members and stakeholders, remain highly motivated, productive, and organized in a fully remote environment.
Ability to travel to international destinations for one week at a time, approximately 2-4 times per year. Locations prior to the global pandemic included New York, Seattle, London, Cape Town, Budapest, Berlin, Montreal, and Brussels.
Nice to have
Experience developing for and deploying on Ubuntu Linux in public clouds.
Experience integrating authentication & authorization, financial, public cloud or marketplace systems.
Experience as a software developer in a high-level language - preferably Go or Python.
We offer
Learning and development opportunities and personal budget
Annual compensation review
Recognition rewards
Annual leave

Title: Senior Software Engineer, C# Front-End
Description:
About Symphony

We've spent the last 8 years building the financial market's largest, most trusted communication network with over half a million users from trading desks to operations and custody teams interacting securely and in real-time on Symphony. Constituting over 1000 institutions across the buy-side, sell-side, securities servicing, and beyond.
But that was only chapter one. We're now using our technology foundation to accelerate far beyond secure collaboration to become the standard connective layer that enables more efficient and automated workflows across the industry to bring the future to financial markets.
The opportunity and our ambition are huge. We need passionate, dedicated individuals to get there. At Symphony we work hard and fast. Our unique blend of technology and financial services makes it an environment you wont get elsewhere.

ROLE DESCRIPTION:
At Symphony, we're on a mission to help people communicate, collaborate and enjoy their work. Our secure messaging and meetings platform is changing the way people do business in information sensitive industries. Our customers are fast-paced, and rely on Symphony to keep up.
Symphony is looking for a Lead Software Engineer based in our Stockholm office. Join our team to contribute to the development of the most secure, compliant, and reliable
communications platform in the financial services industry.
Working as part of a highly skilled delivery-oriented development team, you will be responsible for the design and development of all of our Client Side software. We build complex, concurrent, always-on apps and manage the whole process, and we'd like you to jump right in.

RESPONSIBILITIES:
Design and develop a highly-reliable Windows desktop application
Architect voice communications platform for call processing, recording, and metadata for advanced data analytics
Integrate third party SDKs and hardware peripherals

REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:
Skills and Experience:
5+ years of experience in software development
Strong knowledge of WPF/C# fundamentals, using MVVM and DI Containers
Low-latency, non-blocking Concurrency in .NET Framework 4.5
Messaging over different transports such as REST, Socket.IO, GRpc
Working knowledge of Agile methodologies, scrum, TDD
Not required but huge pluses
HTML5, CSS, Javascript, TypeScript
Angular, ReactJS, Electron
WebRTC, VoIP, SIP, and Telephony
Java Spring/Boot
AWS, Linux
Networking, Websockets, TCP/IP, UDP
Education:
Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering is required, Master's preferred.

Benefits and Perks:
Competitive salary
Bonus Plan
Build your own Benefits (BYOB) perk
Benefits based on location
Many other fun and exciting benefits and activities!
We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment.
Symphony reserves the right of ownership for all unsolicited resumes submitted for this requisition and is not responsible for any fees associated with unsolicited resumes. Symphony participates in E-Verify.

Title: Lösningsarkitekt CRM & Power Platform
Description:
Vill du arbeta med marknadens mest moderna lösningar på ett företag med 100 % fokus på Power Platform och Microsoft Dynamics 365? Vill du jobba i en central roll med att utveckla en lösning för kunden i nära samarbete med duktiga kollegor? Då är jobbet som lösningsarkitekt hos oss någonting för dig!
Innofactor som företag
Innofactor drivs av att modernisera och digitalisera våra kunders organisationer. Vårt ramverk för den moderna digitala organisationen har lösningar för: hur våra kunder når sina kunder digitalt, hur den nya moderna affären drivs, hur en modern arbetsplats realiseras, hur tjänster säkert flyttas upp i molnet, och hur företaget kan dra nytta av ett datadrivet tillvägagångssätt. Vi fokuserar uteslutande på Microsofts ekosystem och våra nordiska experter arbetar i framkant av digital transformation med innovation och implementation av både små och storskaliga lösningar. Vi drivs av att lösa utmaningar och tänja våra gränser, varje dag. På Innofactor kan du utvecklas genom intressanta projekt och genom vårt nordiska nätverk där vi delar passionen för att skapa innovativa lösningar för våra kunder.
Om Rollen
Vi söker dig som är vass på att ta fram lösningar och har ett brinnande intresse för förändringsarbete kopplat till IT. Som lösningsarkitekt ansvarar du för att ta fram och samordna lösningar tillsammans med våra verksamhetskonsulter. Du kommer att vara en viktig kugge i vår verksamhet och framväxt och hos Innofactor kommer du att få tillgång till ett stort antal kollegor med kunskap inom alla delar av Microsofts erbjudande. Majoriteten av våra kunder har sina lösningar i molnet och vi har en strategi att arbeta med kunder som ligger i framkant, som vill ha hjälp med att komplettera sin befintliga IT strategi med en molnstrategi.
Dina arbetsuppgifter kan bl.a. vara:
Ta fram lösningsförslag/design tillsammans med verksamhetskonsulter
Hålla workshops för att analysera kundens nuvarande arbetssätt och behov
Säkerställa implementering av Microsoft Dynamics 365
Kvalitetssäkring av framtagen lösning
Ta fram roadmap för molnstrategi tillsammans med våra kunder

Vem är du?
För att lyckas i rollen bör du arbetat som lösningsarkitekt och varit med i implementationer av system och processer. Som person är du positiv, engagerad, har lätt för att samarbeta och trivs med varierande arbetsuppgifter. Du har ett brinnande intresse för IT som verktyg för verksamhetsförbättringar och har viljan att lära samt söka ny kunskap kring produkter med lösningar som Innofactor använder och levererar. Du är ödmjuk, jobbar verksamhetsnära och drivs av förändringsarbete. Pragmatiskt och kreativt tillvägagångssätt tillsammans med att vara engagerad och lyhörd är nyckelfaktorer för att lyckas som konsult hos oss.
Efterfrågad kompetens
Du har god förståelse för en verksamhets vardag och utmaningar och har förmågan att analysera och utforma arkitektur baserat på verksamhetens krav och kundens perspektiv.
Du har förmåga att driva förändring i både små och stora organisationer och känner dig bekväm i dialogen med beslutsfattare.
Du har erfarenhet av arkitektrollen samt flera års erfarenhet av Microsoft Dynamics och Power Platform.
Du är lyhörd och kan kommunicera på alla nivåer, både internt och gentemot kund.
Du har ett intresse för ledarskap och förmågan att leda team i förändring
Högskoleutbildning eller motsvarande inom relevant område


Vi erbjuder
Innofactor har det bredaste erbjudandet i Microsofts ekosystem med expertkunskap hos 500 anställda i Norden. I Sverige är vi 100 erfarna och engagerade kollegor som arbetar med intressanta och utmanande projekt inom Microsoft Dynamics 365, Office 365, Microsoft Power Platform, Microsoft Data & Analytics platform och Azure. Vi är en Microsoft Gold Partner i 15 kategorier och har fått utmärkelsen Microsoft Dynamics Partner, vilket vi är väldigt stolta över.
Vi jobbar tillsammans, hjälper och utmanar varandra och har roligt på vägen. Tillsammans bildar vi ett starkt team för att möta marknadens krav på innovativa och avancerade verksamhetslösningar. Vårt huvudsakliga uppdrag är att ge både organisationer och individer chansen att göra en skillnad i den digitala världen. Våra kunder befinner sig mitt i sin digitalisering och har ett stort intresse av förändring i form att förbättra och effektivisera sina arbetssätt. På så vis gör vi som konsulter/företag stor skillnad ute hos våra kunder. Arbetsmiljön är kreativ och dynamisk och det är viktigt att du som anställd får en bra balans mellan arbete och privatliv. Vi har våra lokaler på Drottninggatan mitt i centrala Stockholm.


Placeringsort: har kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Sundsvall men söker även dig som önskar arbeta på distans.
Omfattning: Tillsvidare, heltid

Title: Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Architect
Description:
As a GCP Data Architect you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards a data-driven decision. We are all passionate about data!
What You'll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
As a GCP Data Architect, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing optimal technical solutions while focusing on Google Cloud Platform.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients in the decision making of which platform and architecture to use
Integration of different data sources, modeling and loading of data
Optimizing different solutions (data warehouse, data lakehouse, machine learning) depending on the purpose
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills.
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want!
Archicture is highly valued at Capgemini, and therefore we’ve invested a lot in educational architecture programs and communities where architects can share and develop ideas. So, if you’re interested in becoming an either a solutition architect or entreprise architecture, we have learning communities for you.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
What you bring
Knowledgeable in Architecting and designing solutions leveraging GCP components like BigQuery, Dataflow, PubSub, BigTable, Rest API frameworks and Kubernetes (GKE)
Knowledgeable from acting as GCP Architect in Architecting applications and SME in multiple projects
Designing secure and compliance architecture, ensuring operations reliability
Knowledgeable in GitHub, CI/CD (Cloud Build, Terraform)
What we see as qualifying:
Hands on experience from development of various services in either of languages preferably as Java, JavaScript/Node.js, Golang and/or Python
Collaborative software engineering practices (Agile, Scrum, DevOps)
Understanding of event-based and microservice Architecture
Knowledgeable in Infrastructure, Network and Security aspects
ETL, Data movement and Data processing skills
Knowledgeable in handling Big Data, along with Rational and NoSQL databases
Certification on Professional Google Cloud Architect or any other cloud provider architect certificate will be an added advantage
An active member in an Architect community

Title: Data Engineer till Marginalen Bank!
Description:
Motiveras du av att driva transformering där molnresan står i fokus? Trivs du som bäst när du får arbeta med både tekniska lösningar och arkitekturella strategier? Då ser vi gärna att du läser vidare…

Som Data Engineer har du en nyckelroll i bankens resa mot en mer datadriven organisation. Du är en del av Data Automation-teamet inom vår centrala Data & Analytics organisation, där även Data Science och Modellering & Analys-teamen ingår.

Det här är rollen för dig som vill kombinera erfarenhet av hands-on utveckling med arkitektur och strategi.

Rollen är baserad på huvudkontoret i Stockholm men möjlighet till visst arbete hemifrån finns.

Ett urval av dina kommande arbetsuppgifter…

Som Data Engineer arbetar du i ett av våra scrum team inom Data Automation teamet men även med andra funktioner med bankens datastrategi. I rollen arbetar du tillsammans med teamet för att skapa strategier och förutsättningar för Marginalen Banks förflyttning till molnet och möjliggörandet av datadrivna beslut, processer, rapportering och ökad affärsintelligens inom hela banken. Teamet består även av konsulter från andra länder än Sverige. Därav är det ett krav att kunna föra sig i tal och skrift på engelska.

Vem du är…

För att lyckas i rollen ser vi att du har erfarenhet av automatisering, versionshantering och DevOps. Du bör även ha erfarenhet av Azure och några av dess komponenter, exempelvis: Azure Data Factory och Azure Data Lake. Även erfarenhet av Snowflake och GIT är meriterande. Du kanske även har ett intresse och/eller erfarenhet av datamodellering (Data Vault, Kimball, Inmon).

Du är van att arbeta agilt och din nyfikenhet och intresse gör att du ständigt håller dig uppdaterad inom ditt område och på nya tekniker. Du ser lösningar framför hinder och brinner för att kombinera dina tekniska kunskaper med att driva och att påverka. Du trivs att jobba i team, är prestigelös och delar kunskap och hjälper andra på ett ödmjukt sätt.

Vad Marginalen Bank erbjuder dig…

Hos oss blir du en del av en prestigelös organisation där du förutsätts delta aktivt samt påverka processer och rutiner. Vi arbetar agilt och skapar effektiva lösningar och fattar goda och genomtänkta beslut. Vi är innovativa, har hög moral, tänker och agerar hållbart, arbetar proaktivt och driver igenom fattade beslut med en handlingskraft och i tid.

Vårt huvudkontor, mitt i centrala Stockholm, huserar i byggnaden Grönlandet - ett arkitektoniskt mästerverk signerat Sigurd Lewerentz från 1932. Vi har en egen restaurang som lagar ekologisk mat vilket är en extra lyx i vår vardag! Här får du arbeta med medarbetare som känner stolthet, arbetsglädje och delaktighet. Vi erbjuder också personlig utveckling ,volontärdag, tjänstepension, friskvårdsbidrag och hälsoförsäkring vilket bara är några av alla våra förmåner. - Läs gärna mer om vår kultur, våra värdeord och våra förmåner på vår hemsida.

Låter detta som något för dig, tveka då inte att kontakta oss!

Vid eventuella frågor är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande ledare Jonathan Söderström på Jonathan.Soderstrom@Marginalen.se. Då urvalsprocessen sker löpande är du varmt välkommen med din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast den 15-03-2023.

Title: Erfaren .Net Utvecklare
Description:
Vi söker dig som är en erfaren utvecklare som vill jobba med Sveriges bästa konsulter på ett företag med 100% fokus på Microsoft. Hos oss får du möjlighet att utmanas av komplexa arbetsuppgifter och stort eget ansvar. Du får utveckla dig själv och din kompetens genom att jobba i prestigelösa team med kompetenta och stöttande kollegor. Och dessutom ha riktig kul på jobbet!

Innofactor som företag
Innofactor drivs av att modernisera och digitalisera våra kunders organisationer. Vårt ramverk för den moderna digital organisationen har lösningar för: hur våra kunder når sina kunder digitalt, hur den nya moderna affären drivs, hur en modern arbetsplats realiseras, hur tjänster säkert flyttas upp i molnet, och hur företaget kan dra nytta av ett datadrivet tillvägagångssätt. Vi fokuserar uteslutande på Microsofts ekosystem, några exempel på modern teknik som vi arbetar med är Dynamics, Azure och Power Apps. Vi ser att nyckeln till framgång och för att nå uppsatta mål i den digitala världen är samarbete och passion. Våra nordiska experter arbetar i framkanten av digital transformation med innovation och implementation av både små och storskaliga programvarulösningar. Vi drivs av att lösa utmaningar och tänja våra gränser, varje dag. På Innofactor kan du utvecklas genom intressanta projekt och genom vårt nordiska nätverk där vi delar passionen för att skapa innovativa lösningar för våra kunder.
Om rollen
Som Systemutvecklare hos oss kommer du att ha en varierad vardag, allt från att jobba med kravarbete och design till att utveckla de systemlösningar som tas fram. Arbetet innefattar både utveckling i och för Microsoft Dynamics 365 CE med tillhörande transaktionsintensiva integrationer och migrering av tidigare systems data. Största delen av arbetet sker i C# .Net, men du kommer också att arbeta i hela Software Development Lifecycle. Du har en central roll och bidrar till förbättringsarbete med våra olika ramverk och standarder.
Du ansvarar för att:
Översätta verksamhetens behov (krav) till informationsmodell och realiserbara funktioner i en designspecifikation
Utveckla och vidareutveckla Microsoft Dynamics 365 CE utifrån framtagna designspecifikationer
Utveckla och vidareutveckla integrationer utifrån framtagna designspecifikationer
Testa och driftsätta framtagna lösningar
Kvalitetssäkra dina leveranser i projekt för att säkerställa leveransgodkännande
Verka som sakkunnig rådgivare och specialist inom arbetsområdet både vad gäller våra kunder och våra egna konsulter.
Underhålla och vidareutveckla din kompetens inom arbetsområdet
Design och framtagande av lösningsförslag


Om dig
Du är en lugn och metodisk person som sätter stort värde på att förstå kundernas processer och arbetsmetoder för att kunna utforma bästa möjliga lösningar. Vidare är du ödmjuk, verksamhetsnära, tänker gärna i processer, drivs av förändringsarbete och triggas av problemlösning och att leverera rätt kvalité i rätt tid. Pragmatiskt och kreativt tillvägagångssätt är nyckelfaktorer för att lyckas som konsult hos oss. Våra medarbetare kännetecknas av en affärsmässig och kundorienterad inställning, samt förmåga att snabbt ta till sig ny information och omvandla den till kreativa lösningar.


Dina erfarenheter och kompetenser
För den här rollen krävs det att du har högskoleutbildning inom systemvetenskap eller motsvarande eftergymnasial utbildning inom relevant område. Samt dokumenterad erfarenhet av systemutveckling (C# .Net) och god erfarenhet av Microsofts tekniker.
4+ års erfarenhet av systemutveckling i C# .Net
Erfarenhet av att utveckla verksamhetssystem
Du kommunicerar obehindrat på svenska och engelska
Arbetat med integrationer mot andra lösningar
God kunskap om databaser och SQL
Du har praktisk erfarenhet av Microsoft Azure
Arbetat med Scrum eller annan Agil metod
Meriterande
Microsoft Dynamics 365 CE eller andra verksamhetssystem
DevOps, Continuous Deployment, Continuous Integration
Automatiserad Testning

Jira

Vi är en Microsoft Gold Partner i 15 kategorier och har fått utmärkelsen Microsoft Dynamics Partner, vilket vi är väldigt stolta över.

Vårt huvudsakliga uppdrag är att ge både organisationer och individer chansen att göra en skillnad i den digitala världen. Våra kunder befinner sig mitt i sin digitalisering och har ett stort intresse av förändring i form att förbättra och effektivisera sina arbetssätt. På så vis gör vi som konsulter/företag stor skillnad ute hos våra kunder. Arbetsmiljön är kreativ och dynamisk och det är viktigt att du som anställd får en bra balans mellan arbete och privatliv. Title: To our client – Product Manager
Description:
Our client is a Stockholm based start-up, soon to be a scale-up. They offer a B2B SaaS-solution within sales and organization effectiveness, and have customers and users across the globe. Existing customers are mainly international stock listed companies with large sales organisations, typically within retail, telecoms and banking.
The company work agile, digitized, and distributed and are moving fast, with customers and prospects around the globe. Our client love data, digital transformation, mobile applications, software, sales, and growing customer accounts. They are still a start-up, but the possibilities are endless. If you are a self-driven team player and want to be part of an exciting journey, you should be one of them and join as their new Product Manager. The road map ahead is very ambitious, and they would like to among other things explore opportunities within ML/AI and enhance its gamification capabilities.
ROLE DESCRIPTION
You will report to CEO and is primarily responsible for product ownership, road mapping, product vision and product requirements. You will also actively establish and maintain processes and initiatives making sure that product development is being carried out effectively and efficiently.
As team scales Product Manager should be ready to take on Head of Product responsibility.
MAIN TASKS
Establishing, maintaining and communicating product vision
Establishing, maintaining and communicating:
o Product- and team backlogs, and roadmaps
Prioritization of product development initiatives and daily tasks
Define, write and communicate requirements on products, integration and features
Develop and drive the product development way of working in partnership with Tech and
Customer Success
Lead tech team and manage initiatives to create and ship compelling products to new and
existing users
Evaluate opportunities and features from a user-, technology- and business perspective
Incorporate data analysis into the decision-making process and provide regular updates to the
executive team
Ensure and follow up customer and end user satisfaction
Build alignment between Product, Sales, Marketing, & Tech
Manage relationship with outsourced Tech-teams and companies
Manage quality and release management
QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE
Mid/Senior Product Owner/Manager
B2B experience, preferably on an international scene
Interested and skilled in design, UX and mobile application development
Extensive know how in data, data analytics and visualization
5-10 years of experience of software development and agile methodologies
Vast experience of SaaS and cloud from a start-up or scale-up company or similar
Background in Sales tools, CRM, Sales Support System, and/or Sales Performance
Management
Preferably experience of Android/iOS, Flutter, Google Cloud, Kubernetes, Jira, Github
Experience of operations and release management
Fluent in English, both verbal and written. Swedish, and/or Portuguese is appreciated
Flexible working hours as team members and customers may be operating in different
timezone
Primary location is Stockholm and candidates must have a working permit In Sweden
WHO ARE YOU?
You are an entrepreneurial spirit, who loves the challenge of working for a start-up. You enjoy a high paced, international, dynamic environment. You are a digital native. You understand the customer journey. You understand the B2B SaaS business model and have hands-on experience in developing mobile applications. You are ready to lead the tech team, set the roadmap, defining the future and impact UX. And you know how to push a development team on deliveries and quality.
HOW TO APPLY TO THE JOB?
In this recruitment our Client work with Academic Search. For more information about the position, you are welcome to contact responsible recruitment consultant Joachim Marmstedt at joachim.marmstedt@academicsearch.se or 0768 502 732. We interview on an ongoing basis, so we look forward to receiving your application as soon as possible.
Academic Search is one of Scandinavia’s most deserving companies in Executive Search & Interim Management. Our focus is on people with documented managerial and specialist competence and we work closely with both national and international companies with strong brands.

Title: Sales Specialist, Customer & 3rd Party Risk
Description:
About us:
LSEG (London Stock Exchange Group) is more than a diversified global financial markets infrastructure and data business. We are dedicated, open-access partners with a commitment to excellence in delivering the services our customers expect from us. With extensive experience, deep knowledge and worldwide presence across financial markets, we enable businesses and economies around the world to fund innovation, manage risk and create jobs. It’s how we’ve contributed to supporting the financial stability and growth of communities and economies globally for more than 300 years.
Position Summary:
We have an exciting opportunity for a driven, client focused and personable Sales Professional to join our high performing team within the Data & Analytics Division of LSEG. We are looking for someone who has a passion for sales and has a ”hunter” mentality. The Sales Specialist has responsibility for driving the 3rd Party Risk & Compliance business development activity in Sweden, Finland & Baltics (existing customers and named prospects). You will be responsible for a gross recurring and outright sales revenue goal.
What will you be doing?
As a subject matter expert to pre-sales and pursuit activities, you will act in support of Account Managers and Solution Sales focusing on all sales (new, cross-sells, up-sells) for the Risk proposition in a given territory with both existing and new customers. You will lead on deals aligned to specific propositions and serve accounts within a defined territory. The role works in close partnership with internal stakeholders to proactively drive gross sales and revenue.
Develop and manage a sales pipeline in relation to Regulatory Risk and Compliance products and solutions, Worldcheck, Refinitiv Due Diligence, Digital Onboarding etc
Seeks new business or new product sales through new account acquisition and / or penetration of new buyer hubs and delivers against target in assigned territory
Inspires confidence in customers through domain expertise. Integrates knowledge of industry trends and personal experience to deliver value to customer(s). Builds value-add connections within the client organization, leveraging network to facilitate introductions and unlock previously inaccessible opportunities. Proactively thinks through customer workflows and how they can be impacted as a basis for solutions selling and cross-business deal making to maximize contract value
Conducts high-efficiency, high-output prospecting; collaborates effectively with lead-gen, account management, and other colleagues ensuring constant coverage of expansion opportunities and participation in customer life-cycle framework
Excels in advancing opportunities through sales stages; exceeding close rate expectations by anticipating obstacles and late-stage delays, preventing them from disrupting sales. Manages administrative requests such as proposals, benchmark calculators and salesforce related tasks to progress against sales goals at pace and with efficiency
Who are we looking for:
We are looking for a driven and dynamic individual to join our diverse team, we are looking for someone with a good domain knowledge of Governance, Risk and Compliance requirements and workflow. This includes: AML/KYC Screening, Enhanced Due Diligence (EDD) and Regulatory Content within the financial or corporate markets. The successful candidate will be effectively positioning and demonstrating our solutions in this area and through a consultative sales process.
Passion for sales, with a drive and hunger to succeed
Have domain expertise in AML, Client Screening, KYC, Enhanced Due Diligence Superior interpersonal, communication skills and presentation skills (verbal & written)
Have market expertise in financial services or large multi-national corporations and experience in constructing complex solution-oriented deals
Have experience in building strong relationships within large organisations
Understanding of cost justification methodologies relevant to the business and to the buyer, utilizing a value case to differentiate a solution from competitive offerings, building multiple evaluation criteria that are compelling to the buyer and developing business models that can be replicated and used by others
Be able to think about the bigger picture
Be an opportunist
At LSEG, we believe that creating a diverse and inclusive organisation is fundamental to the way we deliver on our promise of creating essential partnerships and open opportunities. Our open culture is central to how we deliver our purpose – driving financial stability, empowering economies and enabling customers to create sustainable growth – in everything we do.
Working with us means that you will be part of a dynamic organisation of 25,000 people across 70 countries. However, we will value your individuality and enable you to bring your true self to work so you can help enrich our diverse workforce. You will be part of a collaborative and creative culture where we encourage new ideas and are committed to sustainability across our global business. You will experience the critical role we have in helping to re-engineer the financial ecosystem to support and drive sustainable economic growth. Together, we are aiming to achieve this growth by accelerating the just transition to net zero, enabling growth of the green economy and creating inclusive economic opportunity.
LSEG offers a range of tailored benefits and support, including healthcare, retirement planning, paid volunteering days and wellbeing initiatives.
We are proud to be an equal opportunities employer. This means that we do not discriminate on the basis of anyone’s race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, veteran status, pregnancy or disability, or any other basis protected under applicable law. Conforming with applicable law, we can reasonably accommodate applicants' and employees' religious practices and beliefs, as well as any mental health or physical disability needs.

privacy notice
carefully, as it describes what personal information London Stock Exchange Group (LSEG) (we) may hold about you, what it’s used for, and how it’s obtained,

.
