As a Data Engineer at EQT you will be working together with Data Engineers, Software Engineers and business stakeholders to revolutionize the core business of EQT and by that, the private equity industry. You will be a part of our Deal Value Stream, a small team dedicated to fighting friction in the way our investment teams find, acquire and create value in portfolio companies.

Why EQT
If you are a passionate technologist who wants to challenge the status quo, and be challenged every day, this is where you need to be. EQT is a purpose-driven global investment organisation with EUR 77 billion in assets under management across 36 active funds. EQT funds have portfolio companies in Europe, Asia-Pacific, and the Americas. EQT works with portfolio companies to achieve sustainable growth, operational excellence, and market leadership. EQT has offices in 23 countries across Europe, Asia-Pacific and the Americas and has close to 1,500 employees.

What you’ll do
Work together with Fullstack Engineers, Application Specialist and Data Engineers to drive development and to ensure a best-in-class investment process
You will be working with your team and business stakeholders to design, implement and maintain data models to quantitatively support everything from performance reporting to improving process efficiency
Have a direct relation with other parts of the business to understand the upcoming business needs. To drive the solution design of both process and systems, as well as implementing it
Be an active part in setting and implementing the technical roadmap to further improve the team’s technical foundation.
Who are you?
Experience working with tools like Fivetran, dbt and Snowflake
Experience in analytics and visualization in BI tools such as Power BI, Looker, Mode etc.
Understanding of master data management, & data ingestion pipelines
Understanding of CI/CD release automation and app integration/orchestration (Workato / Airflow) is creditable
Experience and passionate about building scalable products and working closely to stakeholders
Experience of delivering products from start to finish
Strong communication skills and a team player
Humble with growth mindset
You thrive in a fast paced environment and like to get things done

Key Differentiators for success
Approachable with strong communication and interpersonal skills and with the ability to challenge and bring on other perspectives
Team spirit, strong social competence, straightforward and friendly, yet down to earth
Personal drive and strive for excellence / success / outperformance. A person who walks the extra mile, takes responsibility and wants to deliver high quality
Willingness to develop and learn and train others
Professional work attitude, high work ethics and high energy level, flexible and ability to work under pressure and getting things done independently
Takes own initiatives, be structured and have a strong ability to plan their own work
Professional in approach to the business and demonstrates comfort in interacting with important clients / counterparties, both internal (within EQT) and externally

What’s in it for me?
EQT is a well established company that has worked within its field for a long time. Being one of Europes largest Private Equity firms you will get a stable employer, being proved by EQTs continued growth during the last years of market turbulence. Due to this, EQT offers genorous compensation packages, with an internal career framework giving you the opportunity to grow within the company. It also includes generous pensions, 6 weeks vacation, a great health care allowance. If you have small children, we also offer a domestic allowance program to enable a good work/life balance. There are of course more benefits on top of this, which we would be happy to tell you about when we meet!

Title: Data Engineer to Data Platform and Innovation team
Description:
Are you a passionate Data Engineer with great organizational and communication skills?
We, at Dustin, are now looking for Data Engineers with varied experience levels who have a strong passion to develop their career in the field, make an impact and are curious to experience how it is working with a leading online based IT partner.
Data Engineer to Data Platform and Innovation team
You will be part of the central platform team to build best practice, sharing knowledge as well as delivering main components to the agile value streams teams. The responsibility of the team consists of creating the common building blocks that enables other teams to move faster, this could be related to data ingestion, data pipelines, data integrations, CI/CD pipelines and provide best practice.
The central team will also host demos across agile teams. Moreover, the team will also do exploratory work and make proof of concepts together with the agile team or together with different parts of business to explore new emerging techs or ways of working. Our stack is focused on Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory and Databricks. Python and SQL are the main languages.
We are a tight team that emphasizes testing new things and learning from each other. Being a part of this team; you get the right environment to adopt and continue the self-driven independent approach to test and succeed with a constant access to guidance as and when required. We believe in continually sharing knowledge and believe that your growth with us should not be limited to the individual projects you take.
What you get
Opportunity to make a difference; impart knowledge among teammates, feeding crucial data to analysts, decision-making and playing a pivotal role in organization’s success
Opportunity to build data solutions with real impact using state-of-the-art tools and platforms.
Opportunity to learn and develop within areas outside of your core competence such as solution architecture, data science and project management.
Working in a great, highly skilled team with a “win as a team” attitude and inclusive culture.
Digital First: We believe in flexibility and that we should work from where we are the most effective.
Collective agreements and wellness grants are examples of benefits.
What you have
3+ years of experience from a similar role.
You know SQL and Python, have experience with Spark, ETL, DevOps practices and CI/CD when it comes to data.
3+ years of hands-on experience of cloud data platforms such as Azure Data Lake, Google BigQuery, Snowflake or similar
Problem solving mindset.
Good presentation, organisational and communication skills with fluency in English.
Passion for People & Technology
Recruitment Process
We want a good match! If needed, we will perform multiple interviews, and possibly a case study test.
If you have any questions regarding the position, please contact the recruiter by email at karishma.sindhu@dustin.se or recruiting manager for this role Marcel Beerden, Team Manager, Data & Insights at marcel.beerden@dustin.com.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Aura Cloud is a platform of choice to financial institutions big and small who experience agility in their everyday business. One of the key services we provide to our customers is data related services for orchestration, analysis, visualization, and other decision making.
As a Data engineer, you will be working with enormous amounts of data across multiple business lines in the financial sector leading to actionable insights for our customers.
6 years + experience in handling Data structures and working with data all along.
Very good hands-on experience in Postgres SQL / SQL server, writing complex queries and data extraction logics.
Working with ETL tools, data platforms, visualization tools like Power BI.
Programming knowledge in Java / Python is an advantage.
Exposure to CI/CD automation and DevOps / agile practice is desired.
Exposure to or a keen desire to learn and manage data streams, big data technologies, will be considered a plus.
We have open positions in both Stockholm and Bangalore – candidates who live and work in either of these cities can apply.

Title: Data Engineer - Nyfiken på nya utmaningar?
Description:
Vill du arbeta i en idérik miljö med fantastiska och prestigelösa kollegor som skapar smarta lösningar till den livsviktiga livsmedelsindustrin?
Vill du veta mer? Det hoppas vi..
Om tjänsten
Hej potentiella nya kollega! Om du börjar hos oss så kommer du att få arbeta i en agil modern organisation, där teamwork och kunden står i fokus.

Våra kunder är några av skandinaviens största livsmedelsföretag och våra projekt är roliga, utmanande och leder alltid till en förbättring på något sätt. Är du nyfiken på vad vi har förbättrat hittills? Vi har minskat matsvinn hos en kund och hos en annan har vi analyserat data från mjölkkornas mjölk för att korna ska må bättre.
Du blir..
..en del av vår familj och välkomnas till en arbetsplats där alla ser fram emot att gå till jobbet för vi har kul ihop, hjälper varandra framåt och är prestigelösa. Vi ligger på en 5:e plats på Great Place to Work listan och vi är ett jämställt gäng med 45% kvinnor och 55% män. Hos oss får du möjligheten att arbeta med utvecklande och varierande uppdrag i en framtidsbransch. Du får en bra start hos oss med en mentor som hjälper dig att komma in i arbetet och ett genomarbetat onboardingprogram.

Om dig
Du är en nyfiken person som trivs med att finna lösningar, vågar göra fel och du är omtänksam och delar gärna med dig av kunskaper och erfarenheter för att öka ditt teams kunskaper. Du har tidigare erfarenhet från konsultrollen och gillar att ha kundkontakt. När det är mycket att göra så tappar du inte fokus och du ber om hjälp om du behöver. Du som alla andra vänner i teamet gillar teknik och utveckling och att kommunicera med kunder på svenska och engelska är inga problem för dig.
Din kompetens
Du är en person som tycker om att jobba med data och tillsammans med data scientist så hjälps ni åt att göra djupare och bättre analyser. Du säkerställer att data kan flöda på ett säkert sätt hos våra kunder.
Verktyg
Cloudutveckling – helst Azure (AWS eller google cloud fungerar också)
Data modellering, data warehousing, databaser och ETL/ELT, vi ser gärna att du har automatiserat datawarehouselösningar
Kunskap och erfarenhet av Datapipelines med Python eller Java.
Erfarenhet av Versionskontroll och CI/CD önskas.
Om oss
Elvenite levererar hållbara lösningar för framtidens livsmedelsindustri. Mitt i hjärtat hos några av Skandinaviens ledande livsmedelsföretag kombinerar vi djupt bransch- och verksamhetskunnande med målet att maximera värdet av deras affärssystem och processer. Vi erbjuder dataanalyser och skapar datadrivna insikter och innovation, enkelt sagt, "vi gillar att göra livsmedelsindustrin smartare".
Vi söker dig som gör det du tror på, och är bra på det. Du är nyfiken, redo att utvecklas, vågar göra misstag och du har passion för att skapa förbättringar. Ta chansen och utvecklas med oss!
Det praktiska
1. Vi hoppas att du vill jobba på något av våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg eller Malmö
2. Arbetstid = 100%
3. Vi har fina förmåner och individuella löner
4. Vi vill ha dig så snart som möjligt eller efter årskiftet.
Sista ansökningsdag 21 December

Vid frågor så kontakta therese.gawor@elvenite.se

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
At Trustly, we’re passionate about simplifying the way people pay and get paid online. We’re a licensed payment institution and our B2B products available across Europe, North America and Australia attract global merchants in segments such as e-commerce, telecom, travel, financial services and gaming. In June 2018, private equity firm Nordic Capital acquired a majority stake in Trustly with ambitions to support us in becoming the leading global online banking payments provider.

We are a diverse and fast-growing team with our headquarters in Stockholm, Sweden, and 9 additional offices across Europe and North America. Together we are leading the development of the payments industry and the work you’ll do here will make a great impact.

About the role

Trustly is developing fast and so are the requirements on data being made available for analytics, data science, reporting and BI. The Data Engineering team’s part in this is to provide a platform and tools to enable data producers and consumers to share data in a frictionless way. Trustly’s European data platform is built on GCP using components such as Airflow (Cloud Composer), Beam (Dataflow), BigQuery, Pub/Sub and Google Cloud Storage. We also maintain the company’s dbt Cloud installation to enable Analytics Engineers and other downstream SQL power users to build their own data pipelines and not become dependent on a single data team that does everything. Parts of Trustly’s payment product run on AWS so knowledge about that ecosystem is important to us as well.
What you'll do:
Build and operate Trustly’s data lake on Google Cloud Storage/BigQuery
Develop and maintain batch and streaming data pipelines
Work with transformations of data from one or multiple source systems to feed our analytics and ML applications
Help data consumers within the company find the data they need and assist them with setting up pipelines and exports
Help us identify new use-cases for our data and work with stakeholders from the rest of the organization on how to realize those
Who you are:
MSc Software Engineering or equivalent
At least 1-3 years experience from a Developer role within the field of Data (Data- or Backend/Database Engineer)
Experience from building streaming data pipelines
Experience from building cloud data solutions (Prio1: GCP, Prio2: AWS)
Good coding skills with Python
Proficient in SQL

Title: Data Engineer – Google Cloud
Description:
Vill du skapa molnlösningar för några av Sveriges största företag? Vi söker dig som håller koll på de senaste tekniska trenderna och sätter kvalitet högt när du implementerar det bästa molnet har att erbjuda. Du älskar att skapa värde genom att sammanställa, bearbeta och använda stora mängder data!

Think. Make. Shift
Knowit Experience Stockholm är arbetsplatsen för dig som njuter av uppstartsfasen i projekt, som älskar att gå på djupet och samla så många insikter du kan. Som sedan lika peppad sätter dig för att lösa identifierade problem och skapa helt nya vägar. Du arbetar med personer som har helt olika bakgrunder och erfarenheter. Du är en del av en större digital byrå, samtidigt som du tillhör ett mindre tvärfunktionellt team och alltid kan bolla frågor med ditt kompetensnätverk.
Data Engineer – Google Cloud
Som Google Cloud Partner och Google Marketing Platform Partner kommer du använda tjänster från Googles universum för att utnyttja potentialen hos data från en mängd olika oberoende källor och system. Rollen innebär en hög grad av frihet under ansvar och ett stort inflytande på hur teamet ska utvecklas och drivas i framtiden. Tillsammans med cirka 150 duktiga kollegor här i Stockholm kommer du att arbeta för att positionera Knowit Experience som bäst i stan på att skapa datadrivna kundupplevelser. Du kommer att arbeta nära bland annat analytiker, strateger, utvecklare och designers.

Du kommer arbeta med att:
Sammanställa datakällor för att bygga datalager i molnet.
Utveckla anpassade data pipelines och integrationer.
Underlätta för- och bygga lösningar för förutsägelse, rekommendationer, segmentering och kundbortfall (anti-churn).
Utnyttja möjligheter inom big data med Google Cloud.
Bidra till fler datadrivna uttag inom kommunikation och marknadsföring.

Du guidar och stöttar med lätthet våra kunder i att dra nytta av större delar i Google Cloud-erbjudandet. Du omvärldsbevakar och utforskar möjligheterna i Google Cloud, för att kunna leda teamet i rätt riktning.

Vi ser gärna att du har:
Relevant utbildning och minst två års erfarenhet som molnutvecklare, dataingenjör eller analytiker.
Goda kunskaper i SQL och Python.
Erfarenhet och intresse för BigQuery, Google Cloud Platform och Google Analytics.
Kunskap om ETL och datatransformationsverktyg som Fivetran, Dataform, dbt.
Erfarenhet av REST API:er och versionskontroll.

Knowit Experience erbjuder dig
Det största vi har att erbjuda dig är våra fantastiska medarbetare. Vi stöttar, sporrar och lär av varandra hela tiden. Du får all möjlighet att ta plats, växa och skapa din framtid hos oss – vi värdesätter dina initiativ! Du kommer att ha varierade uppgifter samtidigt som du själv är med och styr din vardag. Distans eller på kontoret? En mix, vi är flexibla. Våra lokaler är moderna och trevliga, anpassade efter olika sorters arbete – fokuserat själv och tillsammans i mötesrum anpassade för kreativa workshops. Kontoret ligger ett stenkast från Centralen och Sergels torg med gym, trevliga restauranger och shopping runt knuten.
Knowit Experience Stockholm är ett självständigt bolag och en del av Knowit-koncernen. Känslan att vara en del av ett litet team, fast med stora karriärmöjligheter och närmare 4 000 kollegor att inspireras av.
Tjänsten är på heltid och tillträdesdatum kommer vi överens om men vi ser gärna att du börjar snarast möjligt. Vi jobbar med löpande urval och ser fram emot att läsa din ansökan. Kanske ses vi över en kopp kaffe eller i ett digitalt möte!

Think. Make. Shift.
Arbetskultur och mer om Knowit som arbetsplats.
Läs vår blogg för att se om vi delar hjärtefrågor

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Want to have the best of two worlds?
We’re looking for data-passionate people to join and build Theodora Tech.
Theodora Tech is a data consultancy firm with a love of data, tech and people. On one hand you get the opportunity to be part of building a startup and on the other hand you get the benefits of the consulting role, like working with the latest technology for some of the most exciting tech companies in the Nordics
The best part? You'll do it together with an awesome, warm and helpful team.
Using our expertise and experience from software and AI-engineering, we help our clients solve problems in and around their data. If you want to be somewhere where everyone knows each other and genuinely cares about one another's careers, let's talk!️

Your Skills and Experiences
As a Data Engineering consultant you will be working with different clients and different tech stacks. We’re looking for a passionate techie with demonstrated experience with for example:
Implementing data pipelines and applications in a general programming language such as Python, Scala or Java
Working with relational databases and SQL (and possibly other database paradigms - you tell us what you’re into)
Building applications in large-scale distributed systems such as Spark
Working towards efficient and maintainable solutions for empowering meaningful business insights from data
Communicating with business stakeholders and encouraging them to use data driven toolsets. You are the bridge between tech and business insights.
Automating testing and deployment using CI/CD best practices using tools such as Jenkins, Gitlab-CI or similar
Working with data governance concepts, such as correctness, freshness, integrity, privacy to boost business confidence in making data-driven decisions

One Team
We help each other. Even though we are currently all on different consulting assignments with different clients, we have Theodora Tech as a common base to stand on. We all have a close relationship with each other, it has been illustrated as a Friends GIF to explain what it is like to work here. We are a good bunch of friends who like to work with data and with each other. We are looking for more people to join this great team and develop the business further.
As a consultant, you have a person who helps you find assignments, write a consultant CV, who will do everything they can to find a client project that suits your wishes and development plan. At the same time, you have consulting colleagues who, like you, can be new to being a consultant or who are experienced consultants and can be a sounding board and cheerleaders.
We all want to help where we can, when it comes to tech issues, stakeholder management, our internal questions such as salary model, recruitment interviews, sales meetings, etc. We are looking for someone who is niched / wants to niche themselves in data and who wants to build a great place to work.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
This is Readly
Readly is a digital subscription service where users across 50 markets have unlimited, “all-you-can-read” access to 7,500 national and international magazines and newspapers - all in one app. Readly has partnered with 1,200+ publishers around the globe to drive the digital transformation in our industry and contribute to thriving societies and a healthy planet.
Our passionate team of 150+ people in Sweden, Germany, France and the UK, have created a value-driven ecosystem where all our stakeholders share the purpose of bringing inspiration and insight into people’s daily lives and unlocking meaningful moments of relaxation.
Since September 2020 Readly is listed at Nasdaq Stockholm.

About the role
We are looking for more data-focused engineers to support our journey towards building more personalized and data-driven products. We currently have two teams who work on ingesting, curating, and preparing data for analytical and operational use. The teams are expected to take ownership of the over full lifecycle of data and support existing data products like recommendation- and search engines. Which team you fit in will depend on your profile and interests. Our cross-functional teams, consisting of data scientists, data engineers and software developers, also work closely with the Analytics- and CRM-teams to create a personal Readly experience in all touchpoints with our users.
At the company we work with the following technologies:
AWS as our cloud service provider
Snowflake (and Redshift) as a data warehouse solution
dbt for data transformation and dependency management
Ruby/Go/Python as mainly used programming languages
Terraform as IaC tool
Step functions for data job orchestration
Gitlab for code versioning and deployment pipelines


What is expected from you
It is expected of you to have a great understanding of the data engineering area as well as basic understanding of the data science area. While it’s not important which service provider, experience working with modern Data Engineering in a cloud environment is essential for the job. Having hands-on experience working with the exact technologies we use is not a requirement although working with similar products within the same area is a must. We have, however, made a bet on Snowflake as our primary data warehouse, so Snowflake experience is a big plus. As we are building a lot of new and exciting services and products, your input on a lot of critical and long-lasting decisions will be greatly appreciated. Therefore, it is important that you have a good level of knowledge about what it means to develop a data product, from data modelling to robust deployment strategies for data pipelines. Good communication skills and ability to work in a team with a culture of knowledge sharing is of course a must as well.

Application
Do you feel this is a perfect match? Please apply by clicking the link below!

Title: SR BI Developer /Data Engineer
Description:
Do you love working with loads of interesting data? Do you have a passion for data modeling? Are you excited to apply your technical skills to analyze this data, and help our teams to get insights from it? Then we would like to welcome you as a Senior BI Developer to our team at Scania.
Our department plays a big role in Scania’s data strategy to deliver top analytical solutions. We enable and enhance data to enforce our employees to perform at their best by providing excellent solutions that increase and secure the right decisions to reach and exceed the business goals.
You will

Be a part of a Squad consisting of developers and a Service Delivery manager working toward a specific business area. You will be part of a ‘’like-minded’’ team that has a passion for working with BI solutions and together you will create a lot of value to the customers. You will be involved and contribute to the CoE’s in the organization.

We work closely with the business (Business&IT as One) and with various stakeholder groups to gather and document reporting requirements to meet business needs. We use scrum methodologies and sprints to follow up on our work. Together with the squad, you are developing the best BI solutions. You will develop tabular models in Visual Studio (SSDT) as well as version management in TFS and creation of tabular model / SSAS, implementation/deployment with BISM Normalizer, documentation, and performance adjustment with built-in and 3-party tools.
In order to succeed in the role, we also see that you have
3-5 years of professional experience in the development of Power BI from start to finish.
Experience in implementing BI solutions using SSIS, SSRS, and SSAS.
You are experienced in working with ETL tooling, Data Warehouse models, and Data visualization.
You have a solid knowledge of SQL Server.
Be able to transform data using SQL tables, stored procedures, and views.
Have good knowledge of requirements collection for reporting installation.
Be able to create advanced DAX metrics and Power Query (M-code) to customize solutions for customers.
We see it as a big plus if you have one or more of the following:
You have experience from a human resources data, finance, or purchase background.
Knowledge of Oracle, Tabular Editor, Cloud, and/or DAX Studio.
Experience and enjoyment of agile methods and DevOps to deliver value continuously.
Academic degree in computer science or equivalent.

Who are you
You add energy to the group and push the team to reach new levels. You take responsibility for your own and the team's development and are happy to drive improvements, within both processes and tools. You are a team player person who dares to take initiative and easy to make yourself adjustable to different situations and work conditions. You are communicating fluently in English and have the ability to connect with users and their representatives, being able to understand requirements and analyze available data and see if it is possible to meet users' expectations and bring clarity to unclear requirements through dialogue. In addition, a person who enjoys having fun with colleagues is much appreciated.

What’s in it for you?

Working from home is nowadays more a fact than a wish and Scania is one of the leading companies on the market that has implemented this approach. We can also mention that we have opened an office hub at Stockholm Sergel where you can work from whenever you like if you are in Stockholm. Furthermore, Scania has a competitive package of benefits, such as a private lease of a car, bonuses, flexible working hours, and much more
Additional information and application

For more information
about the position, please contact Rosiane Andretta-Sundman (Manager), rosiane.andretta-sundman@scania.com or Zanko Dasko (Talent Acquisition Specialist), zanko.dasko@scania.com
Kindly apply as soon as possible with CV and cover letter, but no later than the 18th of February, since selection and interviews might be held throughout the whole application period. Kindly notice that a background check might be done for this position.
We are looking forward to your application!

About Scania
Scania is a world-leading provider of transport solutions. Together with our partners and customers we are driving the shift towards a sustainable transport system. In 2021, we delivered 88,930 trucks, 4,436 buses as well as 11,786 industrial and marine power systems to our customers. Net sales totalled to over SEK 146 billion, of which over 20 percent were services related. Founded in 1891, Scania now operates in more than 100 countries and employs some 54,000 people. Research and development are mainly concentrated in Sweden. Production takes place in Europe and Latin America with regional product centres in Africa, Asia and Eurasia. Scania is part of TRATON GROUP. For more information visit: www.scania.com.

Title: URGENT REQUIREMENT - AWS Data Engineer
Description:
The AWS Data Engineer will deliver high quality data pipelines on the Bank Data Platform. As these are our first steps in our AWS journey, there is a big possibility to contribute to how we work, how we build and how we ensure quality. The AWS Data Engineer will work in close collaboration with the AWS Data Engineer Lead, other Data Engineers and Data Analysts, implementing well-performing, re-usable code with a high degree of quality. Key Responsibilities:

Developing high-quality data pipelines, making data available on the Bank Data Platform. - Create reusable components and enhance existing flows and components. - Provide documentation at the right level, to help others understand and support what you have built. - As we work in a DevOps fashion - be responsible for what you build and for the deliveries of the team as a whole. Professional skills: - Extensive knowledge of the AWS platform. - Extensive knowledge of the AWS Data Lake - related services, ie AWS Glue, AWS S3, AWS Athena, AWS Select and AWS Lambda. - Good knowledge of Kafka integration. - Good knowledge of Datamodelling. - Good knowledge or relational databases. Experience:
Knowledge and experience from development of Data Lakes in AWS, using AWS technologies. - Experience with ELT/ETL tools and processing. - Experience with data lake concepts. - Experience working with data quality. - Experience working with Bank/Finance is an advantage

Title: Senior Data Engineer experience in the banking sector,...
Description:

Start: TBD
Apply: as soon as possible

Stockholm-based consultancy and competence firm with a focus on IT, Management and Technology.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Description
About TriOptima
TriOptima was founded in 2000 in Stockholm and is an award-winning provider of critical post trade infrastructure and risk management services for the OTC derivatives market. Our customers are banks and financial institutions across the world. We design services that reduce risk and cost for the finance sector, always with the highest security at heart and with focus on quality throughout our processes.
TriOptima is a pioneering fintech business at the heart of financial markets, bringing together the people, processes, and network to optimise operations for thousands of firms across the globe.

TriOptima started a new chapter in 2021 as part of OSTTRA, a new venture that unites four businesses that have been at the heart of post-trade evolution and innovation for the last 20 years.
The office space is modern, spacious, and designed for social interactions and our rooftop terrace makes for scenic lunches in the summertime, right in the middle of Stockholm. We will provide you with equipment for remote work and always encourage a healthy work-life balance. We believe our colleagues are fantastic and the most important part of us and our culture. We strive to make this a place where everyone feels like they have a place, can grow, and have fun while doing something valuable.

About OSTTRA
Launched in 2021, OSTTRA unites four businesses that have been at the heart of post-trade evolution and innovation for over 20 years: TriOptima, MarkitServ, Traiana, and Reset. With an outstanding track record of developing and supporting critical market infrastructure, our combined network connects thousands of market participants to streamline end to end workflows - from trade capture at the point of execution, through portfolio optimisation, to clearing and settlement. Learn more at www.osttra.com
Business Analytics team
The team is responsible for the internal and external business analytics. The purpose of the team is to help the organization make informed data driven decisions, as well as identify business opportunities and process improvements. We collaborate closely with business owners and senior management to understand business needs and translate them to actionable insights.
The team takes responsibility for the entire data pipeline. The team manages a data warehouse where we collect data from the TriOptima services as well as external sources which we then use to deliver data to our BI platform and other analytical tools. The data pipeline is written in Python, and we use Tableau as a BI platform.
The team is highly self-driven. We are continuously adjusting our way of working as we find what works for us. We encourage collaboration and continued learning. We believe that diversity is what makes a good team great, and that diversity of experience and thought create inclusive and successful products. As a global company with colleagues around the world we work in English, even in the Stockholm office where the TriOptima technology department is located.
Data Engineer role
As a Data engineer at TriOptima, you are expected to:
Maintaining and supporting our data warehouse
Extending the data warehouse to support exports from new products and services
Develop the business intelligence data platform which includes database design and managing the ELT process.
Collaborate with other technology teams to build robust data integrations
About you
To succeed in this role, we believe that you have experience with some of the following:
Degree in engineering or similar
At least 2 years of experience from data engineering/bi developer within a business intelligence/analytics team
Proficient in programming Python or similar language
Experience of data warehouse design
Experience of ETL/ELT processes and tools
Comfortable writing complex SQL queries. Work effectively with big data volumes in both relational databases and with unstructured data
You are fluent in English, both in writing and verbally
Understanding and interest in the financial market and derivates is a bonus

CME Group: Where Futures Are Made

CME Group (www.cmegroup.com) is the world's leading derivatives marketplace. But who we are goes deeper than that. Here, you can impact markets worldwide. Transform industries. And build a career shaping tomorrow. We invest in your success and you own it, all while working alongside a team of leading experts who inspire you in ways big and small. Problem solvers, difference makers, trailblazers. Those are our people. And we're looking for more.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Vill du vara med och bygga världens bästa e-handelsupplevelse? Vill du jobba med ett team som använder de senaste teknikerna?
Nordic Nest växer så det knakar och vi behöver nu förstärka teamet med en Data Engineer som kan driva utveckling av nästa generations datalager och analysverktyg. Dessa är centrala för att vi ska kunna leverera världens bästa kundupplevelse. Här blir du en del av Techteamet som levererar applikationer som miljontals besökare ser och verktygen som hundratals anställda använder varje dag. Du rapporterar direkt till CTO.
Vi letar efter dig som har arbetat med lösningar som t.ex. Azure Synapse, Redshift, BigQuery eller Snowflake och tycker att molnet är kul att arbeta i. Du har även jobbat med uppsättningar utav ETL/ELT-flöden mellan olika system, både i klassiska on-prem miljöer och i molnet. Att bygga bolagets ”single source of truth” är något du brinner för. I denna roll är du med och bygger vårt nya datalager som ska klara av att hantera datamängder upp till petabytenivå kommande år.
I ditt dagliga arbete kommer du vara en viktig del i processen från design, utveckling och driftsättning. Du driver projekt tillsammans med projektledare och analytiker i verksamheten och ser till att vi alltid har rätt data på rätt plats för att kunna ta bästa beslut.
Vi vill alltid bli bättre och en viktig del i det är code reviews och projektuppföljning som görs löpande, här är vi prestigelösa och uppskattar när vi lär oss något nytt och vill gärna dela med oss av vår kunskap. Vi gillar förändring, öppenhet och vill alltid leverera bra resultat.
Vi ser att du
Har minst 3 års erfarenhet av liknande tjänster
Har universitetsexamen inom relevant område eller har motsvarande arbetslivserfarenhet
Har djup kunskap i SQL
Erfarenhet utav analysverktyg som till exempel PowerBi eller Tableau
Erfarenhet utav något programmeringsspråk som till exempel C#, Python, Scala eller liknande
Har ett analytiskt mindset och gärna säkerställer antaganden med data
Är duktig på att kommunicera skriftligt och muntligt med både utvecklare och icke-tekniska intressenter på svenska och engelska.
Har stark drivförmåga och ser alltid till att ta projekt i mål

Har du dessutom erfarenhet utav något av följande är det meriterande
Erfarenhet utav ML/AI
Erfarenhet utav realtids flöden med strömmande data
E-handel
Vi erbjuder dig en fantastisk rolig tjänst med ett team av kollegor som engagerat kämpar för att utveckla verksamheten. Du kommer att vara en del i ett bolag där kunden alltid kommer i första hand, allt vi gör ska bidra till att skapa nöjdare kunder. Vi är ett bolag i en stark tillväxtfas där du kommer ha en direkt påverkan på vårt gemensamma resultat. Du kommer få arbeta med kollegor som har ett stark driv och ett resultatfokus, vilket gör att vi i perioder jobbar extra hårt och intensivt för att nå våra mål. Det är viktigt att du trivs i en kultur som präglas av ett högt tempo, där vi firar framgångar och jobbar hårt för att skapa dessa.
Välkommen hem!
Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning på heltid.

Vi tror att talang och personliga egenskaper säger mer om din framtida prestation än vad din dokumenterade erfarenhet gör, därför använder vi personlighetstester i ett tidigt skede i rekryteringsprocessen.
Vi kommer gå igenom ansökningarna löpande, så vänta inte med din ansökan.
Varmt välkommen med din ansökan!

För frågor kring tjänsten kontakta CTO Jacob Rastad på jacob.rastad@nordicnest.com .

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
What is this about?
Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions. We understand how Computer Vision and AI can benefit the society. We stand ready to use our expertise to facilitate businesses in their journey into the era of AI. We work with several clients with various industry fields in close collaboration with top universities in Sweden.

Synteda is actively working on several unique products and solutions in various fields. Dream-innovate-create is our work process were our ideas go through different stages. We create successful solutions by checking feasibility of our product idea (POC) and develop our solution working with agile methodologies until we reach a complete full-scale product.

Synteda has a core team of highly qualified experts that provide assessment to identify challenges and explore different ideas to enhance effectiveness and develop specific algorithms to overcome company challenges. Synteda is built on ethical awareness, curiosity, transparency, respect, participation and last but not least science.
What are we looking for?
Responsibilities
Work on our various platforms and customer assignments.
Develop, code and implement data solutions according to requirements.
Maintain data sources, pipelines and models.
Develop Data Quality checks for source and target data sets.
Development and maintenance of ETL/ELT processes.
Enhance existing applications and platforms.
Create project specifications and requirements.
Develop and maintain reports.
Adopt best practices and share them across the team.

Skills
Good knowledge and experience of Python.
Good knowledge with ETL, PowerApps, Databricks, Docker, Delta Lake, Azure Data factory.
Experience with data visualization tools such as Power BI, Tableau, Microsoft Access, SPSS modeler, SAS or similar.
Strong experience with databases like SQL or similar.
Expertise in Hadoop, PySpark, Hive or similar.
Good knowledge of cloud such as Google Cloud, AWS and Azure DevOps for deployment and management of developed models.
Experience in Data modelling.
Experience in Data warehousing.
Experience creating ETL/ELT processes.
Experience creating reports.
Experience of agile development methodologies.
Fluent in English, both spoken and written is required.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
QVIK is a consulting company, 100% owned and run by Qvik’s employee. We design, develop and consult our clients - resulting in digital solutions with real measurable value. We have left our mark e.g. in finance, travel, media, healthcare, gaming, telecom and logistics industries.
Now we are looking for a senior Data Scientist or Data Engineer specialist to join our growing team in Stockholm.
SENIOR DATA ENGINEER
We are looking for ambitious person with significant drive! You should be passionate about your job and enjoy a fast-paced international working environment.

MSc in mathematics, computer science, natural sciences, or related field
Distributed accounting systems

Skilled with Data lake technologies, both cloud and on premise

Problem solving and performance optimization skills

Contribute to the data warehouse design and data preparation, and assemble large and complex data sets
Creating and monitoring models

Work closely with development teams to implement features into production
Improve existing processes for data processing and analytics

We look forward to receiving your application!

Title: Databricks Data Engineer - Malmö
Description:
Interested in belonging to the strongest Databricks community in the Nordics? Learning from experienced architects and getting access to lots of upskilling material and courses? Then we’re looking for you.
What You’ll Do
In your role as a Databricks Data Engineer you will be working with the latest tools within data ingestion, ETL and reliable orchestration for data, analytics & AI. We work with both batch and streaming data that powers analytics dashboards & productionized machine learning models.
As a Global Strategic Partner with Databricks, our close collaboration enables better projects for our clients. In our team deliveries, we can get support from Databricks to ensure quality architecture and better end result.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are also partners with other technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want!
Archicture is highly valued at Capgemini, and therefore we’ve invested a lot in educational architecture programs and communities where architects can share and develop ideas. So, if you’re interested in becoming an either a solutition architect or entreprise architecture, we have learning communities for you.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Spark, Pandas or Azure Data Factory
Experience with the Databricks Lakehouse Architecture
Good understanding of the Databricks Platform
Excellent Python skills
Excellent SQL skills
Good Spark skills
Good skills in DevOps processes with git version control and CI/CD practices
Good communications skills
Ability to work well in a team
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Databricks: Delta Live Tables
Databricks: Unity Catalog
Software Engineering
Experienced with streaming systems
Data Modelling (Data Vault, Star Schema etc)
Test Automation
Experience with setting up Azure, AWS or GCP Infrastructure
Infrastructure as Code tools such as Terraform or Biceps
Spark Query Optimization techniques

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
At Keolis we move people from A to B with the help of advanced technical solutions within the public transport sector. Do you want to be part of and contribute to an important aspect of peoples everyday lif? And have a passion for data and thrive in a company that works towards a sustainable future?
About the role
As a Data Engineer at Keolis, you will have a key role in our tech department and the development of our new Data team. We have just started building our data warehouse and data lake and we now have an execiting journey ahead of us, where you will set the roadmaps for how we will work with data at Keolis. You will be an important leader and a valuable support between both IT and the business to identify the need for data and our way towards a modern data driven organization. As a Data Engineer you will ensure the quality and valuate our data sources and be a part of migrating data to Azure.
As the work with advanced data analysis is in the start-up phase, you would be able to use all your experience and ideas to help us establish this new department. In the role of Data Engineer, you are responsible for building the analysis environments that will be used for machine learning and advanced analysis. You set up ETL processes, build our Data Lake and and identify our data sources. You will also work with our Data Goverence and Data modelling. Our data comes from several different business areas, everything from internal systems to live stream data from our buses. As the team's capabilities grow, so will the applications and new data sources become relevant.
Who are you?
To succeed in this role you have to work independently but appreciate being surrounded by knowledgeable colleagues and have an extraordinary ability to work together. We also believe that you are used to working with data in a Microsoft environment and have experience of retrieving data from different systems. You are also communicatively skilled and have an easy time switching between a holistic and a detailed perspective.
To succeed in this role we see that you have:
A few years' relevant work experience in a similar role
Experience of working with Microsoft products such as Azure, Azure synapse.
Experience of workning with cloud platforms.
Experience of programming languages such as R, Pyhton and
Experience of SQL databases.
Relevant higher education.
Interest and drive to develop both organizations and working methods.
Excellent ability to express yourself in English and preferally Swedish as well.
To work at Keolis
We offer you a thriving and business-oriented industry. Keolis is a global company where you will work for Keolis Sweden. We operate traffic over big parts of Sweden, currently in Dalarna, Karlstad, Uppsala, Gothenburg and Stockholm. In order for us to be able to grow, we need, among other things be able to deliver our services with higher efficiency and quality than our competitors.
As an employeer It is important to us to give you the best conditions for you to both deliver results and at the same time feel good and thrive in your role. You as an employee will receive an individually designed introductory program to give you a flying start.
We offer an exciting work environment characterized by ethnic and cultural diversity where the climate is open and we respect each other. At Keolis, you have good opportunities to combine your professional life with private life and we work actively to promote the development of our staff and grow within the company.

Contact
For questions about the recruitment process, please contact Lina Sylvén who is responsible for this recruitment, email address lina.sylven@keolis.se
For union questions contact:
Klas Wallin, representantive for Unionen at 070-602 67 74 / klas.wallin@keolis.se
Michael Lindqvist, Akademikerföreningen at 072-515 18 60 / michael.lindqvist@keolis.se

Application
Our recruitment takes place on an ongoing basis, we therefore ask you to submit your application in the form of a CV as soon as possible. You do not need to write a personal letter, but we think it is better to get to know each other by talking to each other. The selection is based on your previous experiences and on your inherent personal circumstances. We will therefore take the help of work psychological test tools from Alva Labs. The position may be filled before the application period expires. A warm welcome with your application!

Title: Data Engineer - Stockholm
Description:
We are looking for an experienced data engineer to join our team. You will use various methods to transform raw data into useful data systems. For example, you’ll create algorithms and conduct statistical analysis. Overall, you’ll strive for efficiency by aligning data systems with business goals.
To succeed in this data engineering position, you should have strong analytical skills and the ability to combine data from different sources. Data engineer skills also include familiarity with several programming languages and knowledge of learning machine methods.
If you are detail-oriented, with excellent organisational skills and experience in this field, we’d like to hear from you.
Responsibilities:
Analyse and organise raw data
Build data systems and pipelines
Evaluate business needs and objectives
Interpret trends and patterns
Conduct complex data analysis and report on results
Prepare data for prescriptive and predictive modelling
Build algorithms and prototypes
Combine raw information from different sources
Explore ways to enhance data quality and reliability
Identify opportunities for data acquisition
Develop analytical tools and programs
Collaborate with data scientists and architects on several projects
Analyse and organise raw data
Build data systems and pipelines
Evaluate business needs and objectives
Interpret trends and patterns
Conduct complex data analysis and report on results
Prepare data for prescriptive and predictive modelling
Build algorithms and prototypes
Combine raw information from different sources
Explore ways to enhance data quality and reliability
Identify opportunities for data acquisition
Develop analytical tools and programs
Collaborate with data scientists and architects on several projects
Requirements and skills:
Degree in Computer Science, IT, or similar field; a Master’s is a plus
Previous experience as a data engineer or in a similar role
Technical expertise with data models, data mining, and segmentation techniques
Knowledge of programming languages (e.g. Java and Python)
Azure data bricks
Power BI (especially DAX)
SQL
Data Modeling
DBT
Azure Devops-able to setup CI/CD
Great numerical and analytical skills
Additional Skills:
SCRUM or Agile
Good communication:
With fellow developers
Key users
Stakeholders
Team player
Drive to deliver solutions to our customers.
Location: Stockholm - Fully Onsite no remote option
Experience range: 7-8 years
Language: English (Swedish and Dutch added advantage)
Fulfilment type: Immediate
Additional requirement: The candidate should be in Europe for more than 5 years.
NOTE: By applying to this job you agree that your profile and personal details can be further shared with Stockholm IT Academy's potential clients and partners or any other third parties to find consulting opportunities.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: DATA ENGINEER
Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION
Vi på Sigma Technology Cloud gör en ny satsning och behöver förstärka vårt team med fler Data Engineers!
Sigma Technology Cloud är ett modernt IT-konsultbolag med säte över hela landet. Vi driver idag den nationella Cloud-satsningen inom Sigma koncernen med fokus på Azure och AWS. På 2 år har vi lyckats skapa en bra marknadsposition och ett tätt samarbete med Microsoft och AWS (Amazon Web Services), vilket har gett oss möjlighet att hjälpa våra kunder med allt från utveckling av nya tjänster i molnet till att strategiskt förflytta de till molnet!
För att stärka vårt partnerskap med våra kunder gör vi nu en satsning inom Data då vi ser ett utökat behov av att kunna fortsätta vägleda våra kunder till att bli ännu mer digitaliserade. Detta arbete innebär en mer data-driven organisation och därför söker vi nu fler Data Engineers!
Om rollen
Som Data Engineer hos oss på Sigma Technology Cloud kommer du att arbeta ute hos våra kunder med olika varierande projekt när Data är centralt. Arbetet kan bestå av insamling, analysering, utveckling och transformering av Data. Utöver din roll som konsult kommer du ingå i vårt interna kompetensnätverk inom Data där du tillsammans med ansvarig och kollegor kommer få vara med och bygga upp kunskap inom området.
Om dig
Vi ser gärna att du har minst fem års erfarenhet från IT branschen och arbetat som Data Engineer i minst 3 år. Fördelaktigt är om du även arbetat i någon Cloud-baserad miljö som AWS, GCP eller Azure. Vidare är du tekniskt intresserad och har en passion för Data. Du gillar att dela med dig av din kunskap och trivs att jobba i team men kan också arbeta individuellt. Som person ser vi gärna att du är social, lätt för skratt och tar stort ansvar.
Några tekniker, arbetsuppgifter och plattformar vi gärna ser att du har erfarenhet eller förståelse för är:
Design, utveckling samt underhåll av data pipelines och data arkitekturer
Programmering inom Java och/eller Python
Databaser såsom SQL, NoSQL etc.
Cloudplattformarna AWS, Azure och/eller GCP
Goda kunskaper inom CI/CD automatisering och DevOps/Agile praxis.
Svenska och Engelska är krav.
Vad kan Sigma Technology Cloud erbjuda dig
Som konsultbolag är det viktigt att vara up-to date med det senaste som händer i marknaden, därför står kompetensutveckling högt upp på vår lista. Vi erbjuder kompetensutveckling till alla personer på olika sätt, i form av dedikerade timmar, utbildning, konferenser och individuell coachning. Detta speglar sig i vår kultur där vi skapat en lärande och inkluderande miljö.
Sigma Technology Cloud är ett familjärt bolag som garanterar dig en inspirerande och utvecklande tid där du kommer få arbeta med Sveriges bästa IT-konsulter. Vi är extremt stolta över den kultur vi skapat som bygger på passion, respekt och transparens och kommer göra allt för att få dina drömmar uppfyllda!
