Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Life at Winningtemp

Winningtemp offers the market an unique and revolutionary technology for creating successful work places. This is done by collecting and visualizing real-time data that describes the employee's experience of leadership, meaningfulness, control and joy at work.
Today, Winningtemp consists of a wonderful and ambitious group of 115+ people in the offices in Gothenburg, Stockholm, Oslo and London. The head quarter is newly renovated (of course with a lot of purple) in the middle of central Gothenburg.

At Winningtemp we care about the well-being of our employees and therefore we of course work continuously with our own tool to be an attractive employer. We have grown by over 2100% in recent years and we continue to grow.
By 2024, our goal is to make an impact on more than 4 million people through our product.

So what is the role about?

As a Data Engineer at Winningtemp, you will work with many different internal stake holders, with a focus on maintaining data, creating data tools and improving internal processes within your area.
Your mission is to ensure that our data generates actionable and valuable results for the business, and ultimately our customers. You will have an important role linked to an important mission of ours; to become One Winningtemp throughout the whole organization.

Other areas of responsibilities;
Create and maintain optimal data pipeline architecture
Assemble large, complex data sets that meet functional/ non-functional business requirements
Identify, design, and implement internal process improvements; automating manual processes, optimizing data delivery, re-designing infrastructure for greater scalability
Build the infrastructure required for optimal extraction, transformation, and loading of data from a wide variety of data sources using SQL and DataBricks ‘big data’ technologies
Build analytics tools that utilize the data pipeline to provide actionable insights into customer acquisition, operational efficiency, and other key business performance metrics
Work with internal stakeholders to assist with data-related technical issues and support their data infrastructure needs
Keep our data secured and compliant across national boundaries
Create data tools for business and product team members that assist them in building and optimizing our business operations and product into an innovative industry leader
Work with data and analytics experts to strive for greater functionality in our data system
Your team and manager ‍‍‍

In this role you will work close to our senior Data scientist, Miroslav, someone you will have daily communication with. Miroslav has two PhDs, including one in artificial intelligence from Stockholm University. He has eight years of experience in academia - during which his research was funded by some of the most prestigious fellowships available, including the Marie-Sklodowska Currie Fellowship. Miroslav works in Stockholm, but this position is also available in Gothenburg.
Miroslav is a very appreciated colleague, dedicated and eager to share his knowledge and experience in the field, everything to make you learn as much as possible.
In this role, you will also be working close to all our different departments, meaning you will have collaboration over the whole organization.

You will be reporting to our CFO and be a part of his team. The CFO is situated in Gothenburg.

Are you the one we are looking for?

Winningtemp is the place where we all succeed together, something that you also feel is essential in your daily work, teamwork makes the dreamwork. You are therefor a team player and enjoy sharing ideas and learnings with the people around you.

You appreciate to plan your work well, and always complete what you've started. You set high goals for yourself, and always does what it takes to achieve good results. In addition to that, you look outside the box to think in new ways, meaning you are good at finding solutions to problems that arise. You are up-to-date in your area of expertise, and you have a great interest in always learning more about new techniques and systems within your area.

You have 4+ years of experience in a Data Engineer role, and you have a degree, or its equivalent, in Computer Science, Statistics, Informatics, Information System or similar. You have advanced SQL knowledge and experience working with relational databases, query authoring (SQL) as well as working familiarity with a variety of databases. You have been building and optimizing ‘big data’ data pipelines, architectures, and data sets. You have been working with structured and unstructured datasets, and you are used to build processes supporting data transformation, data structures, metadata, dependency, and workload management. You have successfully manipulated, processed, and extracted value from large disconnected datasets.
You have experience in using one and/or several following software and tools:
Big data tools: Spark (preferred), Hadoop, Kafka, etc.
Relational SQL databases
Data pipeline and workflow management tools
Azure Databricks, Data Factory or similar
Object-oriented/object function scripting languages: Python, R or similar
Experience with business intelligence tools, for example Power BI
Nice to haves:
HR tech platform/tool industry experience
Previous experience from working in a start up/scale up
No worries if you do not experience in all of the areas and/or tools, we will guide you along the way!

What's in it for me?
A fun and evolving opportunity to learn a lot and to actual have an impact, both professionally and on a personal level
Committed and dedicated colleagues, and closest manager, who not only laugh together at work, but also outside of work at events, AWs, kickoff etc.
Be a part of the journey and innovation of a scale up providing a meaningful product for our customers
30 days vacation and advance holiday
Generous wellness allowance
Great pension and insurance offer


Why Winningtemp?

As an employee at Winningtemp, you will be part of our purple family
With us, you will find energetic and loyal colleagues who help each other succeed together. With us, everyone is equally valuable, regardless of gender, ethnicity and background. Diversity is also something we work actively with and something we value. We share happiness every day, not only for our product and the work we do, but also for each other. The commitment of each employee is what really makes us stand out from other companies. You can expect a supportive workplace where everyone works together towards our vision; to forever change how people succeed together!
We promise you; you will be impressed!

Our recruitment process includes;

Personality and logical test -> Interview with recruiter -> Interview with the future manager -> Interview with closest colleague -> Reference check -> Offer

We handle applications continuously so don't hesitate to apply as soon as possible!

Title: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
Our team is new and we sit in Volvo Cars new Tech Hub in MOOD in central Stockholm. We operate in a start up alike environment, but with the resources and support that only a big company can offer. Our team is a part of the Global Online Experience (GOX) area and our mission is to ensure we know our customers well and keep this information safe and secure.

We have only just begun this journey in earnest, and you’ll be joining us at a time where you can really make a great impact. We are having fun, have a highly innovative atmosphere, and are excited about our emerging ecosystem of data products. You will help us to form our data platform from the beginning and play a key role in defining our tech stack. We think you would love to join us if you are passionate about modern data architecture principles, data technologies, and data storage solutions and want to apply your interest to improve the experience for all of Volvo Cars customers. Come join us and set the tone for the next chapter in our company's and the entire automotive industry’s history!

What to look forward to as a part of our team

We are in an early stage and there are plenty of opportunities in the team to drive experiments and build innovative tools that will help us to build a cloud based world-class data architecture based on Data Mesh principles. Your work will be creative and you will help us to leverage our large and diverse datasets to enable use cases with direct impact on the end-customer's digital experience. The heart of the role is to design, code, test, and document programs using agreed standards and tools to achieve well-engineered results. You will work closely with data producers and product teams to share your knowledge and identify improvement areas and to build domain expertise that will help us to deliver on our exciting product objectives.

Who you can be

We are keen on building a team with a diverse set of skills and the most important is that you are a team player, passionate about data engineering and wants to join us on our journey. It’s great if you have strong programming fundamentals and are experienced with architecting large-scale distributed computing systems in the cloud. It’s also valuable if you have experience designing and building distributed data pipelines and have worked with data modelling, data access, and data storage techniques. The role includes working with many different stakeholders and speaking with many different teams and we hope you enjoy that and are interested in delivering value to the business together with your team members.
Application

We are continuously screening applications and will fill the position as soon as we find a good match. We encourage you to apply as early as possible For questions regarding the recruitment process, please contact Senior Tech Recruiter, Lovisa Ermell, lovisa.ermell@volvocars.com . Please note that applications via email will not be accepted.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Electrolux Professional presents:

DATA ENGINEER
Ljungby, Sweden

As part of the Electrolux Professional team, one day is never the same as the next. But what drives us every day is our mission to make our customers’ work-life easier, more profitable – and truly sustainable. Becoming their OnE trusted partner, managing their complete operations. Understanding their daily journey – and making it a winning one - whether they run a hotel, restaurant, laundry or café. Acting truly sustainable means going beyond products; connecting users with intelligence, humans with technology and innovative thinkers with relevant business models. And providing the most inclusive service offering with expertise, state-of-the-art interfaces and the best people network. Together with you, we will grow and create sustainable experiences for people and the world around us, in food, beverage and laundry.

A REGULAR DAY AT WORK
In this role you will evaluate and develop new technology solutions for our professional laundry, food and beverage appliances. You work in the Advanced Development (AD) team located in Ljungby, Sweden, in close collaboration also with colleagues of the AD team in Vallenoncello, Italy. Cross-functional collaboration is a vital part of your work, in particular with Product Managers, the Design, the Electronics, the Product Development and the Lab teams, as well as Purchasing and Production. Your work environment is truly international, serving all five Business Areas (see About Electrolux Professional, below) with R&D teams and production sites on three continents. Therefore digital work tools and remote collaboration is a natural part of your work and some business travels occur. But you will also spend a lot of time in the physical world, doing experiments and testing prototypes in our modern and spacious lab in Ljungby.

YOUR MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES
Lead the activities related to data analysis and machine learning within an AD project.
Create models based on noisy and non-linear data (understand and formalize problem, create dataset, create and train models,…).
Implement the integration of models into a product together with control system specialists.
Proactively align objectives, tasks and technical aspects with your colleagues.

YOU
Are Customer Obsessed - You actively listen to understand our internal and external customers’ needs and deliver value.
Build Trust - You are accountable, share information and take ownership of your area of specialty.
Are Bold - You can work independently without detailed directions. You get things done. You are not afraid of making mistakes and you learn from them.
Act sustainably - You always act in an ethical and responsible way, and you have sustainability in mind in whatever you do. You build for the future.
You are curious about people and about stuff. You want to learn, to improve and to build something bigger together with others.

EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE
Degree (master or higher) in data science / computer science / mathematics / software or other engineering.
Specialization and practical experience in machine learning and other data analysis methods.
At least 2 years of practical experience, more desired.
Good general programming skills
Experience with Raspberry Pi is a plus
Good proficiency in written and spoken English. Swedish communication is a plus.

Please apply by: 31.12.2022

About Electrolux Professional
Electrolux Professional is one of the leading global providers of food service, beverage and laundry for professional users. Our innovative products and worldwide service network make our customers’ work-life easier, more profitable – and truly sustainable every day. Our solutions and products are manufactured in 13 plants in seven countries and sold in over 110 countries. In 2021, Electrolux Professional had global sales of SEK 7,9bn and approximately 4,000 employees. Electrolux Professional’s B-shares are listed at Nasdaq Stockholm. From July 1, our global business is divided into five Business Areas (BA): BA Beverage & Food Preparation, BA Laundry, BA Food Americas, BA Food APAC & MEA and BA Food Europe.
For more information, visit https://www.electroluxprofessional.com

Title: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
Vill du jobba i ett företag med både hjärta och hjärna som satsar mycket på IT? Vill du forma innovativa och smarta IT-lösningar i agila team som skapar trygghet och värde för våra kunder?
Du kommer ingå i ett tvärfunktionellt utvecklingsteam för att sammanställa ändamålsenlig rapportering och analys inom Folksam. Teamet jobbar med fokus på att leverera högkvalitativ data och analys som är till stor affärsnytta för både våra interna användare och externa kunder. Teamet ansvarar även för att utveckla och förvalta den tekniska plattformen. Folksam står inför många förändringar där dataflöden byggs om för att anpassas till nya regulatoriska krav samtidigt som den tekniska plattformen behöver moderniseras och konsolideras. Vi söker nu erfarna Data Engineers som ska förstärka befintliga och nya team i vår förändringsresa.
Det här gör du som Data Engineer på Folksam
Vi arbetar för bland annat med att förflytta vår tekniska plattform för Data Warehouse från en IBM-plattform till en molnlösning baserat på Azure och samtidigt utveckla vårt sätt att se på data pipelines och värdeskapande analyser och data.
Hos oss bygger, förvaltar och vidareutvecklar vi Folksams tekniska lösningar inom Data & Analys och samarbetar med leveransens produktägare och intressenter. Vi jobbar enligt SAFe och det team som du kommer jobba i är ett av flera som ingår i ett agilt releasetåg.
De tekniker som vi arbetar med idag är framförallt DataStage för IT/ETL och vi vill förflytta oss mot Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, Python, Testautomation och Power BI. För att lyckas i rollen behövs ett mycket bra samarbete dels med det egna teamet och med andra team och intressenter. Du förväntas vara kvalitetsmedveten och vill förstå den data som du arbetar med. Därutöver krävs självledarskap, nyfikenhet, vilja att lära och hitta vägar för att skapa värde.
Är du den vi söker?
Vi söker dig som idag arbetar som Data Engineer, Systemutvecklare eller motsvarande. Du har flerårig erfarenhet av komplext beslutsstödsarbete med verktyg såsom IBM DataStage, Informatica, MS SSIS eller Azure Data Factory.
Erfarenhet vi värdesätter för den här rollen är:
Erfarenhet från arbete i Microsoft Azure.
God erfarenhet av Azure Data Factory, Delta Lake-arkitektur samt utveckling av data pipelines.
God erfarenhet av DevOps-utveckling med CI/CD pipelines samt jobbat med Infrastructure as Code i Bicep, Terraform eller motsvarande.
Behärskar programmeringsspråk såsom Python, Scala, R eller SQL.
Erfarenhet av datalager och datamodellering, som till exempel data vault och dimensionsmodellering.
Erfarenhet inom utveckling av ML-lösningar i cloud-miljö såsom Azure.
Erfarenhet av teknologier, metoder eller verktyg såsom Hadoop, Spark, MLflow, Power BI eller SAS.
Erfarenhet av Databricks, API:er, kodtestningsramverk.
Erfarenhet av datahantering i SQL.
Utvecklas tillsammans med oss
Folksam är ett kundägt företag med stort fokus på hållbarhetsfrågor. Vi har många roliga, utvecklande jobb och bra förmåner. Vi tror på ett hållbart arbetsliv och hos oss har du goda chanser till en spännande karriär. Vi erbjuder flexibilitet att varva arbete på kontoret och hemifrån utifrån verksamhetens behov. Våra trevliga kontor runt om i landet ger mötesplatser för samarbete, lärande och en gemensam kultur – tillsammans skapar vi engagemang och kraft framåt! På folksam.se/jobb-och-karriar/ kan du läsa mer och se filmer om hur det äratt jobba på Folksam.
Så söker du jobbet
Välkommen att skicka in din ansökan redan idag, men senast 13 februari 2023. Intervjuer sker löpande under ansökningstiden.
Vill du veta mer om jobbet är du välkommen att kontakta någon av rekryterande cheferna Jacob Karmehag, 072-468 71 83, jacob.karmehag@folksam.se eller Henrik Nose, 070-831 52 82, henrik.nose@folksam.se
Fackliga representanter: Akademikerföreningen Per Hansson 070-831 60 67, Forena Morgan Svensson 073-423 59 12 och Handels Mikael Carlsson 070-831 51 32.
Folksamgruppen erbjuder försäkringar och långsiktigt sparande som skapar trygghet i livets alla skeden. Vi är cirka 4 000 medarbetare och vår vision är att våra kunder ska känna sig trygga i en hållbar värld. Vi engagerar oss i det våra kunder bryr sig om och är måna om att de är rätt försäkrade.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
IMPORTANT: Please note that we are only considering candidates with business-level proficiency in Swedish. This is due to requirements on us from our customer base.

Vi har pågående projekt inom DW cloud (Azure Synapse, Azure Data Factory, Azure SQL etc.),Big Data (Cloudera/HDP) och DW on premise (MSSQL/SSAS/SSIS/Power BI). Trots vikande konjunktur har vi fullt upp och nya affärer dyker upp hela tiden. Vi tycker det är roligast att jobba med en mix av välbekanta och nya teknologier, vilket ger ett konstant lärande i skarpa miljöer och vi har ett mycket bra track record med detta angreppsätt.
Vi är ett blandat gäng med killar och tjejer samt många bakgrunder som för närvarande jobbar med uppdrag inom bank, försäkring, energi och trossamfund – och vi är extra stolta över uppdrag hos kunder med en allmännyttig funktion och strävar efter att jobba med kunder vars värderingar vi delar. Vi tror på balans mellan arbete och fritid och vi är gärna flexibla med var vi sitter och arbetar.

Analyticsteamet ingår i ett av XLENT-bolagen i Stockholm som är ett gäng systemutvecklare, projektledare och kravanalytiker. Vi är en del av Xlent Consulting Group med hundratals duktiga konsulter över hela Sverige (och lite i Norge). Detta gör att vi kombinerar det lilla företagets fördelar i form av noll internpolitik, tröga processer etc., med styrkan hos ett större företag med delade kostnader och möjlighet att bemanna projekt med resurser från många olika XLENT-bolag.
För att passa för tjänsten bör du ha god kommunikativ förmåga i tal och skrift och känna dig bekväm med att jobba nära verksamheten. Du är erfaren nog att arbeta självständigt och du får gärna ha erfarenhet av mentorskap. Du erbjuds stora möjligheter till personlig utveckling i våra spännande projekt och bör ha en stor aptit på nya utmaningar.
Flytande svenska i tal och skrift är ett grundkrav. Högskoleexamen är meriterande.

Title: Cloud Data Engineer
Description:
Som Cloud Data Engineer är du ansvarig för att se till att alla data- och analystjänsterna i våra lösningar byggda på Microsofts moln-ekosystem är effektiva, högpresterande, pålitliga och välorganiserade.

Huvuduppgiften är att vägleda, stödja och leverera en modern data- och analysplattform till våra kunder så att de kan släppa lös kraften och potentialen i sitt datainnehav.
En dag på jobbet
Du kommer att få möjlighet att integrera, transformera och konsolidera data från olika strukturerade och ostrukturerade datasystem till strukturer som är lämpliga för att bygga analyslösningar.
Du kommer att guida och hjälpa våra kunder att förstå data genom att utforska, bygga och underhålla säkra och kompatibla databehandlingspipelines genom att använda olika verktyg och tekniker.
Personliga egenskaper och erfarenheter som säkerställer att du briljerar i denna roll
Du är säker på begreppen relationell och icke-relationell data, och olika typer av workloads som transaktionella eller analytiska samt hur de implementeras med hjälp av Microsoft Azure-datatjänster.
Du besitter gedigna kunskaper i databehandlingsspråk, och förstår konceptet parallell bearbetning och dataarkitekturmönster.
Du är intresserad av att utforska AI-lösningar som utnyttjar Azure Cognitive Services, Azure Cognitive Search och Microsoft Bot Framework.

Title: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
VI
Vi söker en ny kollega som vill fortsätta vår resa inom datadrivet tillsammans med oss! Våra kunder är allt ifrån den lilla som är precis i början på att upptäcka och arbeta datadrivet till den stora som har kommit en bit på vägen och behöver specialistkompetens. Ibland sitter vi internt i team och ibland som expertkompetens i kundens team, vi tror på lärande och varierande uppdrag för konsultrollen. Just nu söker vi en senior Data Engineer som kan kroka arm med vår kollega Jon Erik Kemi Warghed som driver datadrivet hos oss på Knowit Solutions i Göteborg. Jon Erik arbetar som konsultchef och Head of Data hos oss och har en bakgrund som Data Engineer och Data Scientist. Vi är på en resa där vi expanderar vårt team inom Datadrivet och vill ha med dig i vår utveckling. Vi ser att du vill vara med att skapa de bästa förutsättningar för data engineering inom vår organisation men också arbeta med att driva kunder i sin resa framåt.
Läs om hur vår kollega Mikaela Giegold tycker det är att arbeta som Data Engineer hos oss:

"Jag sökte mig till rollen som Data Engineer för att på ett varierat sätt få möjlighet att arbeta med data. Dels genom att djupdyka tekniskt vid implementation av pipelines och lagring, diskutera hypoteser och utföra analys men också stötta kunder i att se på sin data som en tillgång istället för en biprodukt".

För att få en känsla kring vilka vi på Knowit Göteborg är, lyssna in här!
DU
Du har ett genuint intresse och förståelse för hur man arbetar datadrivet. Vi ser att du vill ligga i framkant inom området och strävar efter att producera bra och smarta lösningar i ditt arbete. Du har minst sju års erfarenhet inom området och har suttit med att samla in data och molnlösningar. När det gäller tekniken ser vi att du har god kunskap inom Python och har haft ansvar över ELT pipelines. Du har arbetat med Docker, cloud, CI/CD och har intresse för både molntjänster som open source tooling. Du har förmågan att vägleda kunder runt arkitektur för sin data stack och kan ta lead i den implementationen. Du kan även gå in och ta ägandeskap över en datadomän och projektleda agila team.
OSS
Vårt mål är att bli det mest uppskattade it-konsultbolaget av både medarbetare och kunder! Med hjälp av medarbetarbestämmande, transparent kommunikation samt individuell och gemensam kompetensutveckling kommer vi att lyckas. Vi sätter ribban högt för medarbetartrivsel och att utvecklas och ha kul tillsammans. Vi har också förståelse för livspusslet och strävar alltid efter att skapa en hälsosam balans mellan arbete och fritid.
Skicka in dina kontaktuppgifter så ses vi över en fika på vårt nya kontor!
Har du några frågor om tjänsten, tveka inte att höra av dig till Jon Erik Kemi Warghed på jon.warghed@knowit.se eller Gabriella Sumberaz

Title: DevOps / Data engineer
Description:
About us
Koalitionen is an IT-consultant company that delivers high-quality consultants to a few of Sweden's biggest companies in various industries.

What do we provide?
We are continuously striving to provide the best conditions for our colleagues as well as for our consultants. At Koalitionen we value hard work and always strive to deliver the best possible results to our clients.

Who are we looking for?

We are looking for you who have in-depth competence and interest in DevOps/data engineers. In your role, you work both with the implementation and management of various abilities that belong to the product. You will be the bridge between the Data Scientist, Data Analyst, and the rest of the IT function.

Assignment background
We are looking for a data engineer for Group staff digitization, IOC, platforms, and DevOps who wants to be involved in developing future patient, resident, and employee services. You will contribute by building new abilities and working with service development to better understand and meet the needs and demands of our residents and employee services now and in the future.
Assignment
As a DevOps/data engineer, you will be part of the DevOps team belonging to the department Infrastructure and Cybersecurity, Unit Platforms. Your assignment will involve designing, developing, testing, and maintaining robust, secure, and scalable solutions for the storage and processing of data, using data pipelines and automation. With the guiding principle of "automate everything" you will help create solutions for the deployment of both infrastructure and platform capacity for both internal and external use.

Requirements
Good knowledge of SQL/NoSQL, ETL/ELT development.
Experience building pipelines and automation.
Experience/knowledge in python
Experience with data modeling
Good understanding of DevOps methodology and agile working methods.
Have the ability to express yourself well in speech and writing in both Swedish and English
The position will be security classified, which requires Swedish citizenship
You are welcome to apply whether you are a sub-consultant or are looking to be employed.

Title: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
Substorm is a consulting and development company in the field of Intelligent Automation. We create customer value in the Digitization area through change management and technology development. We offer understandable solutions and create data-driven insights with the help of techniques from AI / machine learning, RPA and Business Intelligence. We also conduct research activities within Agenda 2030's global goals for sustainable development, specifically No. 5 Gender equality and No. 9 Sustainable industry, innovations and infrastructure.
We drive change and are eager to co-create benefits with modern technology and smart analytics. We bring fun and efficiency back to our customers daily work, and do it with algorithms, automation and extensive business knowledge.

We have offices across Sweden, from Luleå in the North to Stockholm and Gothenburg in the South - and we want to grow!

We are now looking for Senior Data Engineers to join our team.

You will work with data processing and data warehousing and help build our infrastructure for use both as stand-alone services and as part of bigger Machine Learning projects. You will be part of implementing the architecture enabling our data science projects, our business reporting requirements and our visualization needs.
We believe that you have worked as a Data Engineer for a few years and that you have previous experience of consulting in the field. You have a university degree in data engineering, computer science, machine learning or other relevant fields, or have proven experience achieved by other means. We also believe that you:
Have strong experience in advanced data structures, distributed computing, ETL/ELT, SQL and SQL transformations
Have strong experience working with cloud based platforms and services
Are excited to take ownership and share knowledge with colleagues and customers
Have an agile mindset and know and care about a CI/CD way of working


It is a plus if you have knowledge of Machine Learning tools and algorithms, and experience in building and designing large scale end-to-end applications and services.
As a person, you are enterprising, solution-oriented and caring. You can explain business value and benefits with your ideas and solutions in a professional way, are a true team player and are always ready for learning new technologies and skills.

Our company is growing fast and offer great opportunities for learning and variety in your work.

Candidates are expected to hold a valid work permit for the EU and Sweden.


More about Substorm
Substorm consists of developers, business analysts as well as automation strategists. We organize our work based on the customer’s need but preferably we deliver as a team. Technology is in our backbone, but we always adjust to our customers actual need. Our day to day work is fast-paced and exciting with a lot of heart and engagement. Conferences overseas, after works and other more or less spontaneous events spices up our work - and we have a lot of fun together!

Title: Azure Data Engineer - Malmö
Description:
As an Azure Data Engineer you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards data-driven decision-making. We are all passionate about data!
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are partners with different providers of technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Azure Data Factory
Experience in Data Lake or Lakehouse Architecture
Excellent SQL syntax skills
Information- and Data Warehouse modeling
Good skills in code versioning such as GIT GitHub, DevOps
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience from platform modernization
Experience from Tabular cubes and DAX
Databricks
Snowflake
Experience in Snowpro, Matillion or DBT
Data vault modeling
Agile work process

Title: SR BI Developer /Data Engineer
Description:
SR BI Developer /Data Engineer
IT
Sodertalje
, SE
2023-02-18

Do you love working with loads of interesting data? Do you have a passion for data modeling? Are you excited to apply your technical skills to analyze this data, and help our teams to get insights from it? Then we would like to welcome you as a Senior BI Developer to our team at Scania.
Our department plays a big role in Scania’s data strategy to deliver top analytical solutions. We enable and enhance data to enforce our employees to perform at their best by providing excellent solutions that increase and secure the right decisions to reach and exceed the business goals.
You will
Be a part of a Squad consisting of developers and a Service Delivery manager working toward a specific business area. You will be part of a ‘’like-minded’’ team that has a passion for working with BI solutions and together you will create a lot of value to the customers. You will be involved and contribute to the CoE’s in the organization.

We work closely with the business (Business&IT as One) and with various stakeholder groups to gather and document reporting requirements to meet business needs. We use scrum methodologies and sprints to follow up on our work. Together with the squad, you are developing the best BI solutions. You will develop tabular models in Visual Studio (SSDT) as well as version management in TFS and creation of tabular model / SSAS, implementation/deployment with BISM Normalizer, documentation, and performance adjustment with built-in and 3-party tools.
In order to succeed in the role, we also see that you have
3-5 years of professional experience in the development of Power BI from start to finish.
Experience in implementing BI solutions using SSIS, SSRS, and SSAS.
You are experienced in working with ETL tooling, Data Warehouse models, and Data visualization.
You have a solid knowledge of SQL Server.
Be able to transform data using SQL tables, stored procedures, and views.
Have good knowledge of requirements collection for reporting installation.
Be able to create advanced DAX metrics and Power Query (M-code) to customize solutions for customers.
We see it as a big plus if you have one or more of the following:
You have experience from a human resources data, finance, or purchase background.
Knowledge of Oracle, Tabular Editor, Cloud, and/or DAX Studio.
Experience and enjoyment of agile methods and DevOps to deliver value continuously.
Academic degree in computer science or equivalent.

Who are you
You add energy to the group and push the team to reach new levels. You take responsibility for your own and the team's development and are happy to drive improvements, within both processes and tools. You are a team player person who dares to take initiative and easy to make yourself adjustable to different situations and work conditions. You are communicating fluently in English and have the ability to connect with users and their representatives, being able to understand requirements and analyze available data and see if it is possible to meet users' expectations and bring clarity to unclear requirements through dialogue. In addition, a person who enjoys having fun with colleagues is much appreciated.

What’s in it for you?

Working from home is nowadays more a fact than a wish and Scania is one of the leading companies on the market that has implemented this approach. We can also mention that we have opened an office hub at Stockholm Sergel where you can work from whenever you like if you are in Stockholm. Furthermore, Scania has a competitive package of benefits, such as a private lease of a car, bonuses, flexible working hours, and much more
Additional information and application

For more information
about the position, please contact Rosiane Andretta-Sundman (Manager), rosiane.andretta-sundman@scania.com or Zanko Dasko (Talent Acquisition Specialist), zanko.dasko@scania.com
Kindly apply as soon as possible with CV and cover letter, but no later than the 18th of February, since selection and interviews might be held throughout the whole application period. Kindly notice that a background check might be done for this position.
We are looking forward to your application!

About Scania
Scania is a world-leading provider of transport solutions. Together with our partners and customers we are driving the shift towards a sustainable transport system. In 2021, we delivered 88,930 trucks, 4,436 buses as well as 11,786 industrial and marine power systems to our customers. Net sales totalled to over SEK 146 billion, of which over 20 percent were services related. Founded in 1891, Scania now operates in more than 100 countries and employs some 54,000 people. Research and development are mainly concentrated in Sweden. Production takes place in Europe and Latin America with regional product centres in Africa, Asia and Eurasia. Scania is part of TRATON GROUP. For more information visit: www.scania.com.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION
Vi på Sigma Technology Cloud gör en ny satsning och behöver förstärka vårt team med fler Data Engineers!
Sigma Technology Cloud är ett modernt IT-konsultbolag med säte över hela landet. Vi driver idag den nationella Cloud-satsningen inom Sigma koncernen med fokus på Azure och AWS. På 2 år har vi lyckats skapa en bra marknadsposition och ett tätt samarbete med Microsoft och AWS (Amazon Web Services), vilket har gett oss möjlighet att hjälpa våra kunder med allt från utveckling av nya tjänster i molnet till att strategiskt förflytta de till molnet!
För att stärka vårt partnerskap med våra kunder gör vi nu en satsning inom Data då vi ser ett utökat behov av att kunna fortsätta vägleda våra kunder till att bli ännu mer digitaliserade. Detta arbete innebär en mer data-driven organisation och därför söker vi nu fler Data Engineers!
Om rollen
Som Data Engineer hos oss på Sigma Technology Cloud kommer du att arbeta ute hos våra kunder med olika varierande projekt när Data är centralt. Arbetet kan bestå av insamling, analysering, utveckling och transformering av Data. Utöver din roll som konsult kommer du ingå i vårt interna kompetensnätverk inom Data där du tillsammans med ansvarig och kollegor kommer få vara med och bygga upp kunskap inom området.
Om dig
Vi ser gärna att du har minst fem års erfarenhet från IT branschen och arbetat som Data Engineer i minst 3 år. Fördelaktigt är om du även arbetat i någon Cloud-baserad miljö som AWS, GCP eller Azure. Vidare är du tekniskt intresserad och har en passion för Data. Du gillar att dela med dig av din kunskap och trivs att jobba i team men kan också arbeta individuellt. Som person ser vi gärna att du är social, lätt för skratt och tar stort ansvar.
Några tekniker, arbetsuppgifter och plattformar vi gärna ser att du har erfarenhet eller förståelse för är:
Design, utveckling samt underhåll av data pipelines och data arkitekturer
Programmering inom Java och/eller Python
Databaser såsom SQL, NoSQL etc.
Cloudplattformarna AWS, Azure och/eller GCP
Goda kunskaper inom CI/CD automatisering och DevOps/Agile praxis.
Svenska och Engelska är krav.
Vad kan Sigma Technology Cloud erbjuda dig
Som konsultbolag är det viktigt att vara up-to date med det senaste som händer i marknaden, därför står kompetensutveckling högt upp på vår lista. Vi erbjuder kompetensutveckling till alla personer på olika sätt, i form av dedikerade timmar, utbildning, konferenser och individuell coachning. Detta speglar sig i vår kultur där vi skapat en lärande och inkluderande miljö.
Sigma Technology Cloud är ett familjärt bolag som garanterar dig en inspirerande och utvecklande tid där du kommer få arbeta med Sveriges bästa IT-konsulter. Vi är extremt stolta över den kultur vi skapat som bygger på passion, respekt och transparens och kommer göra allt för att få dina drömmar uppfyllda!

LOCATION

System development, Software development, Digitalisation, Digitalisation

Data integration, data structures, data pipelines and data management in the cloud
SQL and Python

Terraform

Om Nordic Leisure Travel Group
En arbetsplats med ett stort kunnande, högt tempo samt en drivkraft att hela tiden bidra till att förbättra vår verksamhet. Ett företag där vi har roligt och bryr oss om varandra med visionen ”The best weeks of the year”.
Vi erbjuder en spännande och utvecklande miljö och vi sitter på Kungsholmen i centrala Stockholm med goda kommunikationer. Hos oss får du som anställd unika reseförmåner då vi tycker det är viktigt att du ska få se den produkt som du arbetar med. Vi har dessutom ett högt medarbetarengagemang som år efter år visar sig i vår interna medarbetarundersökning. Vi älskar vårt jobb och välkomnar dig ombord på vår resa i Nordic Leisure Travel Group!
Varmt välkommen med din ansökan!
Nordic Leisure Travel Group som består av researrangörerna Ving, Globetrotter, Spies, Tjäreborg, flygbolaget Sunclass Airlines samt hotellbolaget Hotels & Resorts (inkl. Sunwing Family Resorts, Ocean Beach Club och Sunprime Hotels), har funnits i över 50 år och är idag Nordens ledande resebolag. Vi erbjuder klassiska paketresor, egenpaketerade resor med reguljärflyg samt kryssningar. Under ett normalt år säljer vi runt 1,5 miljoner resor i de nordiska länderna.

Title: (Senior) Data Engineer(s) - The future of banking with...
Description:
Finna Group is partnered with one of Sweden's largest financial institutions and their innovation centre which is challenging the old norms of how banks and financial institutions ship and develop software.

Current vacancies are:

Mid and Senior Data Engineers

Short description of responsibilities involved:
Initiate and drive new projects scaling and developing their data stack
Build cloud scalable, real-time and high-performing data solutions leveraging GCP
Build sustainable capabilities for data reporting, data analytics, data governance, data quality and metrics in all aspects of the business
Create and drive implementations of data management projects to support the target architecture
Coach and guide junior colleagues


Being part of a large bank the salaries and benefits are the best I've seen from any business in Stockholm including; staff rates on mortgages, loans, stocks in the product, market-leading pension schemes, holiday rentals and a whole load of perks and discounts with their partners.

All engineers joining the team will be part of building the next generation of financial services. They are building an organisation and culture of highly autonomous product teams with the innovation power to give our customers the future of banking.

Being autonomous but with the backing of a large bank, they are on a mission to challenge and explore both new technologies and new business opportunities.

Their tech stack is fully on GCP, they're using BigQuery as their data warehouse and Looker as their data exploration and visualization tool. Their data pipelines are built using Kafka, Apache Airflow and Apache Beam with dbt as a tool for modelling data.

This is a great opportunity to put a stamp on some brand new products and work with a truly pragmatic team of engineers.

Apply for more details.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.
For further information see www.babyshop.com
ABOUT THE POSITION
Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organization, where it acts as the foundation to our everyday work; whether it being more traditional reporting about what has happened, ad-hoc analysis to understand why that happened, or highly complex machine learning models to predict what will happen. We truly believe that one of the key factors of gaining a competitive advantage in a highly competitive market, is through the use of our data. As a Data Engineer, you will join the Data Team consisting of people with different expertise; Data Warehouse Developer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We use a combination of Fivetran and Apache Kafka to load data into our DWH Snowflake as well as DBT for transformation. Here you will get your hands dirty to understand and transform data using SQL for downstream tasks, ranging from analysis, to BI, to advanced ML use-cases. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO
Develop an understanding of source data as well as end-user needs, and use that to transform data into appropriate formats.
Collaborate with the other members of the Data Team to leverage data end-to-end, from discovering and connecting new data sources, load and transform, to be used for use-cases within BI/ML.
Use CI/CD best-practices together with version control to develop our dbt-workflow.
Use SQL best-practices to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, high performant code.

WHO YOU ARE
You have a passion for data & tech and appreciate a fast-paced entrepreneurial start-up vibe.
You have experience with relational databases and an excellent understanding of SQL.
You have experience in database design and modeling for data warehouse and business intelligence applications.
You are interested in keeping up to date with technological advancements within the data field, and are not afraid to try out new tech.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...
Have previous experience with dbt, and dbt Cloud.
Have previous experience with Snowflake.
Have previous experience with CI/CD and version control.
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Data Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.
Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28, however, applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!
Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Data Engineer till Marginalen Bank!
Description:
Motiveras du av att driva transformering där molnresan står i fokus? Trivs du som bäst när du får arbeta med både tekniska lösningar och arkitekturella strategier? Då ser vi gärna att du läser vidare…

Som Data Engineer har du en nyckelroll i bankens resa mot en mer datadriven organisation. Du är en del av Data Automation-teamet inom vår centrala Data & Analytics organisation, där även Data Science och Modellering & Analys-teamen ingår.

Det här är rollen för dig som vill kombinera erfarenhet av hands-on utveckling med arkitektur och strategi.
Rollen är baserad på huvudkontoret i Stockholm men möjlighet till visst arbete hemifrån finns.
Ett urval av dina kommande arbetsuppgifter…

Som Data Engineer arbetar du i ett av våra scrum team inom Data Automation teamet men även med andra funktioner med bankens datastrategi. I rollen arbetar du tillsammans med teamet för att skapa strategier och förutsättningar för Marginalen Banks förflyttning till molnet och möjliggörandet av datadrivna beslut, processer, rapportering och ökad affärsintelligens inom hela banken. Teamet består även av konsulter från andra länder än Sverige. Därav är det ett krav att kunna föra sig i tal och skrift på engelska.
Vem du är…
För att lyckas i rollen ser vi att du har erfarenhet av automatisering, versionshantering och DevOps. Du bör även ha erfarenhet av Azure och några av dess komponenter, exempelvis: Azure Data Factory och Azure Data Lake. Även erfarenhet av Snowflake och GIT är meriterande. Du kanske även har ett intresse och/eller erfarenhet av datamodellering (Data Vault, Kimball, Inmon).
Du är van att arbeta agilt och din nyfikenhet och intresse gör att du ständigt håller dig uppdaterad inom ditt område och på nya tekniker. Du ser lösningar framför hinder och brinner för att kombinera dina tekniska kunskaper med att driva och att påverka. Du trivs att jobba i team, är prestigelös och delar kunskap och hjälper andra på ett ödmjukt sätt.
Vad Marginalen Bank erbjuder dig…
Hos oss blir du en del av en prestigelös organisation där du förutsätts delta aktivt samt påverka processer och rutiner. Vi arbetar agilt och skapar effektiva lösningar och fattar goda och genomtänkta beslut. Vi är innovativa, har hög moral, tänker och agerar hållbart, arbetar proaktivt och driver igenom fattade beslut med en handlingskraft och i tid.
Vårt huvudkontor, mitt i centrala Stockholm, huserar i byggnaden Grönlandet - ett arkitektoniskt mästerverk signerat Sigurd Lewerentz från 1932. Vi har en egen restaurang som lagar ekologisk mat vilket är en extra lyx i vår vardag! Här får du arbeta med medarbetare som känner stolthet, arbetsglädje och delaktighet. Vi erbjuder också personlig utveckling ,volontärdag, tjänstepension, friskvårdsbidrag och hälsoförsäkring vilket bara är några av alla våra förmåner. - Läs gärna mer om vår kultur, våra värdeord och våra förmåner på vår hemsida.
Låter detta som något för dig, tveka då inte att kontakta oss!
Vid eventuella frågor är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande ledare Jonathan Söderström på Jonathan.Soderstrom@Marginalen.se. Då urvalsprocessen sker löpande är du varmt välkommen med din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast den 15-03-2023.

Title: Data Engineer (f/m/d)
Description:
Data Engineer
About the Role
We strongly believe that in this digital age for a sustainable competitiveness it is imperative to have a strong focus on Data & Analytics cutting across Business Services. We are heavily investing in areas like Big Data, Data Science, Reporting, and BI Tools to meet our Digital transformation objectives. We are looking for an experienced professional in the role of Data Engineer to help us in achieving the same. In this role of Data Engineer, you will work across various Data & Analytics Tools, Applications, and Big Data Platforms.
You feel ownership (and are responsible) for the data, as key company asset and driving, govern, and guide teams and know how to maximise value and balance speed and quality in delivery. You are aware about the best practices in Data & Analytics domain and you know the best way to utilise them or you are keen to learn and share your findings with others. As part of the Analytics Microsoft Delivery team you will be working closely with Data Science, Enterprise Architecture, and Business Unit teams to contribute towards the data strategy; as well as with Application Architects and Solution Architects to implement coherent solution architecture and learn from each other.
We’re looking for people who embody our values, aren’t afraid to challenge, innovate, experiment, and move at a fast pace. We’re always looking for ways to improve our products and ourselves. If this is you, we’d love to talk.
What You Will Do
Contribute to delivering business impact and finding and implementing effective solutions in a matrix organisation to drive the enterprise information strategy and analytics transformation
Take a leading role in operationalising data science models to ensure all requirements, including functional, integration, security, performance, quality, and operations are covered
Be responsible for implementing projects and develop, build, configure, unit test, and implement data solutions based on lower level designs within the data infrastructure
Ensure data solution technical functionality and meet requirements outlined in the design in terms of scalability, security, performance, data recovery, reliability, etc.
Align and implement measures to ensure data accuracy and accessibility
Constantly monitor, refine, and report on the performance of data management systems
Implement system configuration changes based on defined solution
Ensure that developed solutions are peer reviewed and formally documented according to company IT standards
Unit test solutions to ensure that they meet quality standards
Maintain, support and repair solutions to ensure performance in accordance with technical and functional specification
Cooperate with other data engineers to make sure that the applications meet requirements and performance goals
Who You Are
University degree in computer science, management information systems, or related discipline
Significant experince of application programming (python or Scala) and ETL/ELT experience
Experience with big data technologies including Hadoop, Apache Spark • More than two years working experience with Databricks and Microsoft Azure Data Lake tools (Azure Data Lake, Azure Databricks, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Warehouse, Power BI, Logic Apps)
More than one year working experience building automation pipelines for testing and deployment using Azure DevOps
Experience working with creating restful APIs and creating external applications to run data science models
Expert in a combination of Spark (Python, R or Scala), PySpark, Spark SQL, Pandas, and/or Spark Streaming
Advanced knowledge of Python to be able to perform code refactoring
Experience in big data tools (Elastic Search/Solr and Kafka) is a plus
Basic understanding of data science
Jupyter Notebooks experience is nice to have
What We Can Offer You

Title: Forward-deployed Lead Data Engineer
Description:
Who We Are

Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we work closely with clients to embrace a transformational approach aimed at benefiting all stakeholders—empowering organizations to grow, build sustainable competitive advantage, and drive positive societal impact.

Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives that question the status quo and spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting, technology and design, and corporate and digital ventures. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, fueled by the goal of helping our clients thrive and enabling them to make the world a better place.

Practice Area Profile

BCG GAMMA combines innovative skills in computer science, artificial intelligence (AI), statistics, and machine learning with deep industry and functional expertise. The BCG GAMMA team is comprised of world-class data scientists, software and data engineers, as well as product experts with a consulting mindset.
We specialize in creating competitive advantage for our clients through AI driven transformations. Our teams own the full analytics value-chain end to end: framing new business challenges, designing innovative algorithms, implementing and deploying scalable solutions, and enabling colleagues and clients to fully embrace AI. Our product offerings span from fully custom-build to industry specific leading edge AI software solutions.

What You'll Do

As a forward-deployed Lead Data Engineer, you’ll be part of our rapidly growing engineering team and help build the next generation of AI solutions. You’ll have the chance to partner with clients in a variety of BCG regions and industries, and on key topics like climate change, enabling them to design, build, and deploy new and innovative solutions. Additional responsibilities will include developing and delivering thought leadership in scientific communities and papers as well as leading conferences on behalf of BCG GAMMA.
WHO YOU ARE
We are looking for talented individuals with a passion for data engineering, software development and transforming organizations into AI led innovative companies
Apply data engineering practices and standards to develop robust and maintainable solutions
Actively involved in every part of the software development life cycle
Experienced at guiding non-technical teams and consultants in best practices for large-scale data engineering
Motivated by a fast-paced, service-oriented environment and interacting directly with clients on new features for future product releases
Enjoy collaborating in teams to share software design and solution ideas
A natural problem-solver and intellectually curious across a breadth of industries and topics



What You'll Bring (Experience & Qualifications)

REQUIREMENTS
Masters degree or PhD in computer science (or in a highly related area)
8+ years of relevant industry experience
Previous consulting experience and/or strong leadership positions
Experience in data engineering and working with global and remote agile squads
Proficiency with analytic software programming ideally in python, C++, or SCALA
Fluency with the storage, manipulation, and management of relational, non-relational and streaming data structures, specifically SQL, Spark, and Hadoop
Proficiency with infrastructure as code principles
Experience working on AWS, Azure, or Google cloud infrastructure
NICE TO HAVE
DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD, Terraform
Understanding of parallel computing
Full stack development: GraphQL, React, JavaScript, TypeScript
Data Science and machine learning (Pandas, Scikit learn)
WORK ENVIRONMENT
Fluency in English is required as well as fluency in the local language for most locations
Ability to travel based on client and business needs. Expect 30-50%

Title: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
Are you tired of working in monotonous environments? Do you want to build a strong resume with advanced technologies and well-known companies? We are the answer! At SwedQ, the employee is always the priority, we listen to your preferences when it comes to your career path - Do you want to be certificated in AWS? We provide it. Do you want to build your own Team? Do it. Do you want to become a Solution Architect in the future? Let's achieve your goals together by designing a role that fits you, your wishes are our law.
SwedQ is a consulting company that works towards becoming the first choice within development and digitalization through delivering tangible results based on our clients conditions and business objectives. We accomplish this by focusing on the Know-how, experience and right competence.
What's in it for you?
As a Senior Data Engineer with SwedQ you will get exposed to bleeding edge technologies, varying environments and challenges each day. We are hiring before having an assignment, we design the role together based on your preferences and experience. Our assignments and solutions are provided throughout all types of industries, but our main focus is within the IT sector. For now, our consultants are working on everything from implementing a new architecture of a cloud solution, to helping to set up the new back end system for autonomous vehicles.
Our clients
The limit is infinite. We work with smaller fintech companies to the more known companies in Sweden. Currently our consultants is working with: Spotify, H&M, Scania, Ericsson, Schibsted among many others.
You will bring:
Minimum 5 years of experience working as a Data Engineer.
Strong analytical / problem solving skills
Good communicator
Fluent English
Experience with cloud solutions like Azure, AWS, GCP.
Experience from building data pipelines in a cloud environment.
Good knowledge of at least one programming language, Java, Python, C++
Experience of Big Data, Hadoop Ecosystem, HortonWorks, Cloudera, spark
Experience with some ETL-tools: SSIS, DataFactory, Informatica, ODI, Talend
Experience with modern way of working: Microservices, serverless frameworks, Containerisation (docker and orchestration with kubernetes)
Understanding of different database structures, NoSQL, SQL, MongoDB etc.
Note that you do not need to fill all of the above requirements, we will be taking into account other aspects of your experience as well!

SwedQ culture
Our culture is very, very important to us, we value low hierarchy, independence and responsibility, value-creating work and having fun together. We believe in diversity and equal opportunity. At SwedQ we want you to be yourself and we value the differences in people, come to the office in flip flops or high heels, as long as you feel comfortable.
We believe in having fun and making memories, to maintain that we do a lot of activities such as playing football tournaments, going on trips and organising dinners.

Competitive salary
Flexible working hours
Budget to spend on health and gym
Generous developers budget
Fully paid relocation package - Work permit, flying tickets & the service to find apartment.
Monthly payments into you additional pension fund
Health insurance
Office in the City – Stone's throw from public transport and lunch restaurants
Support for open source projects and community engagements
Developers time, to use during work hours for your personal growth
Kick-ass colleagues and mentors at every corner
Other information about the employment
Start - Immediately / as soon as possible
Employment - Full time
Location - Stockholm

Title: Azure Data Engineer - Gothenburg
Description:
As an Azure Data Engineer you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards data-driven decision-making. We are all passionate about data!
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are partners with different providers of technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Azure Data Factory
Experience in Data Lake or Lakehouse Architecture
Excellent SQL syntax skills
Information- and Data Warehouse modeling
Good skills in code versioning such as GIT GitHub, DevOps
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience from platform modernization
Experience from Tabular cubes and DAX
Databricks
Snowflake
Experience in Snowpro, Matillion or DBT
Data vault modeling
Agile work process

Title: Lead Data Engineer
Description:
Vill du vara med och växa med oss på B3 Business Transformation? Vi söker nu en duktig Lead Data Engineer!
B3 Business Transformation stärker våra kunders digitala konkurrenskraft genom att vara datadrivna i sina processer, analyser och vid beslutsfattande. Med vår kompetens inom Advanced Analytics, Data Warehouse, Business Intelligence i kombination med stor affärsförståelse leder vi våra kunder in i ett datadrivet arbetssätt och möjliggör utveckling av nya digitala initiativ och etablering av moderna arbetssätt.
Om rollen
Som Lead Data Engineer är ditt fokus att designa, modellera, utveckla datalager och integrationsflöden från en eller flera olika källsystem för att lagra data i strukturerade och/eller semistrukturerade datakällor. Din uppgift är att framgångsrikt driva lösningar i mål på egen hand eller i grupp och med olika typer av kunder i olika branscher. Du arbetar med kompetenta kollegor där ni tillsammans formar en effektiv informationslösning vilket är en förutsättning för att skapa ett bestående datadrivet arbetssätt hos kunden.

Vad vi kan erbjuda dig:
Vi har en stark och dynamisk företagskultur, och tror på balans i livet. Som konsult hos oss kan du själv vara med och påverka din ersättning, arbetstider, kompetensutveckling och vilka slags uppdrag du vill ha.
En ökad komplexitet inom våra kunders IT-miljöer ställer höga krav på våra specialistkompetenser. Även våra produktpartners kräver att vi håller oss uppdaterade om deras teknologier. Därför är det viktigt för oss att ge dig möjlighet att löpande utbilda och certifiera dig inom relevanta områden för att behålla eller öka ditt marknadsvärde.
Om dig
Vi ser gärna att du har erfarenhet av att arbeta som Data Engineer både on-prem och i cloud-baserad miljö. Du har förmågan att lyssna och ta till dig kundens behov men också vara en god kommunikatör som kan övertyga och skapa enighet runt en lösning i en utvecklargrupp. Vidare får du gärna ha kunskap och erfarenhet av flera olika moderna ramverk och utvecklarverktyg för ETL/ELT-flöden, Databaser, Data Warehouse, DataLake, Datamodellering och DevOps.
Du behärskar affärsmässig svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift.
Du har kunskap inom några av nedanstående tekniska plattformar, lösningsmönster och verktyg:
Databaser – SQL-Server, Readshift, BiqQuery, Snowflake, etc.
ETL/ELT – Data Factory, SSIS, Talend, Stitch, Wherescape, etc.
SQL-utveckling/kodning
Power Shell, Python
Cloud-plattformar – Azure, AWS, Google
Informationsmodellering, Dimensionsmodellering, Data Vault
Data Management
Analysplattformar DevOps (CI/CD) - Jenkins, Git, etc.
Machine Learning i Python, R, Scala
