Title: Data Engineer to Tracab!
Company: Ants Akademiskt Nätverk av Tekniska Studenter AB
Description:
Data Engineer
Join the team responsible for developing the real-time sports tracking system that runs at major soccer arenas every match day. TRACAB’s image tracking system is the world’s most accurate optical player tracking system and is used by top football leagues across the world. TRACAB covers all games in the FIFA World Cup, Bundesliga and LaLiga.

If you are a Data Developer who is passionate about utilizing the value of data to drive cutting edge products, and enjoy working in a dedicated close-knit team, we would love to hear from you.

The Role:
You will have responsibility for building and maintaining a machine learning database to support the ongoing improvement, analysis and testing of AI products for the professional sports market. You will work closely with our developers to create functionality and tools to harness the large quantities of data we have available.

This role is with TRACAB’s Computer Vision and Machine Learning team in Stockholm, Sweden.

Requirements:
Experience working with setting up and maintaining a database for machine learning containing large amounts of data, including images and video.
Familiarity with best practices for achieving this both in the Cloud or on a local NAS.
Knowledge of how to make the data access fast, easy and efficient for developers.
Experience with setting up automatic data handling scripts, e.g. to update, analyze and curate data.
Experience with a Cloud platform such as AWS, Azure, Google Cloud.
Desirable (nice to have): Experience with:
technologies such as Jenkins, TeamCity, Bitbucket Pipeline etc.
setting up continuous integrations in Visual Studio-based environments (C++)
setting up complex test environments that run unit tests, short-running tests (10 min) and long-running tests (10+ hours) on multiple agents.
cloud testing
As a person you will be positive, self-motivated, and a team player.

What we offer
A job where you will keep abreast of the latest developments in data handling for machine learning.
An opportunity to work with and extend the state-of-the-art in sports data analysis.
You will work with data from the world’s most prestigious and demanding clients in sport, including. FIFA, Bundesliga, La Liga, Eredivisie, …
A flexible hybrid working environment with a focus on work-life balance.
Does this sound interesting? Then you should apply right away! If you have any questions regarding the role or ChyronHego, do not hesitate to contact Clara Hornbek at clara.hornbek@tracab.com

Title: Software Engineer (Telemetry) - Games
Description:
As our Telemetry Engineer at Embark you are a key person to ensure that the Data Science team has all the information necessary to understand and improve the high-quality, polished experiences we want to provide to our players. The current team consists of a Telemetry Engineer and a Senior Data Engineer and in close collaboration with them you will define and implement telemetry events in the game.

We think you have a background as a Software Engineer and an interest in data. The game we're making is built in Unreal, using C++, blueprints and a scripting language called Angelscript. The Role is flexible and can either be focused on working with Unreal Engine and C++ or to be leaning towards working with the Go backends, data pipelines and making automation tools. We believe in your ability to cleave your own path and ways of working.

Example of responsibilities
Implement telemetry events and develop the framework for sending telemetry within the game code base using C++ and Rust
Work closely with the Game Designers and the Data Science team to design and create telemetry specifications
Build tools to make the data more available to our data engineers and data scientists
Create and automate test systems to reduce manual quality testing
Extending the Telemetry Viewer plugin in Unreal Engine
We would love if you have
A creative and curious mind
Love for data
Strong Experience with C++, Rust or similar languages
Interest in or experience from working with game engines, e.g. Unreal or Unity
Basic knowledge of SQL
A good grasp of performance, optimization and data structures
The ability to be a great team player with good communication skills
Professional English communication skills.
Experience from game development is meritorious
At Embark we offer competitive salaries, passionate colleagues to share knowledge with and much more, but most of all we invite you to take part of a journey into the unknown, to build creative, surprising and beautiful experiences together.

We welcome game makers of all sex, class, colour, age, gender identity, education, religion, opinion, culture, nation of origin, language, sexual orientation, shape, size, and ability.

Did we leave anyone out? Well, we welcome you, too! We think that the gaming industry is made better when everyone has a seat at the table.

Be yourself at Embark and make games while doing so. Please apply with confidence. We can’t wait to hear from you (in English)!

If this role doesn't quite match what you're looking for, feel free to apply to us via our "Open Application."

Title: Connect with us for future jobs in software development at Storykit!
Description:
Founded in 2018 in Stockholm, we are expanding the universe of video content creators from hundreds of thousands of video editors, to hundreds of millions of storytellers world wide, who can now create video.
We are the complete video creator busy changing how the world thinks about and works with video.
Storykit is constantly growing! At the moment we are not actively recruiting but you are welcome to amaze us with your application for future opportunities in both employment, ex job (thesis) and summer jobs. Please clarify in your application what type of employment you are looking for!
How you will make life easier for hundreds of millions of storytellers worldwide:
At Storykit we have a broad range of roles within the tech area, so depending on your ambitions and skillsets we can see opportunities to work with fullstack development, or as a specialist with focus on either frontend, backend or video engineering.
You will be part of our ever-evolving team of developers, sometimes spending months designing and implementing new exciting features for our customers. And then mixing that up with investigating edge cases for customers or optimizing performance.
(Please note that we are not actively recruiting through this ad and therefore the response time may vary. We will get back to you as soon as possible and when we find an interesting opportunity!)

What about the tech?
We're developing the front end of our web application in Angular 12 with TypeScript and NGXS.
Our backend runs in a NodeJS runtime environment with microservices architecture. It's hosted on Heroku and AWS with GitHub Actions for CI/CD. We develop all new features in TypeScript, while some old features are still in JavaScript (we're continuously rebuilding those using TS). On the database side, we're using MongoDB with Mongoose as ORM. However, we also use PostgreSQL for our Data/AI solutions.
Additionally, we develop one part of our rendering cluster in Rust + Kubernetes.
Please note that we don't expect you to have experience working with all the tech we use, instead we hope you want to grow in your role with us!

What about the team?
Glad you asked! Team spirit and collaboration are super important for us and currently, we're around two dozen developers working together to make our product great.
We're divided into three functional teams that have full-stack competence, hence they are responsible for everything from designing the feature to implementing and testing their code. We manage our projects using a mix of Scrum and Kanban.
Video - handle all parts of our rendering cluster as well as new slide types/layouts
Data/AI - create features that automatically recommend video content for our users (layouts, text, music, stock images/videos from our library, etc.)
Organize - are responsible for developing Video Studio (our video editing application) and the Creative part of our tool. This includes functionality for handling accounts, user data, different accesses, etc.

We also have a cross-team that includes functions that work with several teams (such as DevOps, UI/UX, CTO, Engineering Manager) and one UI Engineer that works mainly with our website storykit.io.

What can you expect from us?
At Storykit, you can expect a safe and open-minded environment that is both challenging and ambitious. We are growing tremendously fast and therefore give all employees a lot of responsibility from day one.
We set high goals, but also make sure that everyone has the right support to be able to reach them. Due to our fast growth, there are almost endless opportunities for development in the organization. You will work in an awesome team, and with generous terms & conditions.

Who are we looking for - really?
We're looking for developers with various seniority levels and experiences who want to connect with us for future possibilities at Storykit (and who wants to focus on either backend, frontend, full stack or video/rendering).
To be a good match, we believe that you:
Have a degree within a MSc or BSc in Media Technology, Computer Science, Systems Engineering or similar. If you're looking for a thesis job, it can potentially be in our interest as well
Have some experience working with TypeScript/JavaScript or Rust (either via work, school projects or in personal projects)
Are comfortable communicating in English
Are authorized to live and work in Sweden (via work permit, EU citizenship, permanent residency or similar)
Bonus
Experience in Angular 2+ and NodeJS
Furthermore, you generally have a strong belief about using the right kind of tool for the right problem and are skeptically curious about new frameworks, libraries, and programming languages

Join the fun!
Storykit is a hybrid remote company, and as a member of our team, you would work either full-time or part-time from our HQ in central Stockholm (we have a very flexible hybrid work policy).
We hope you’re up for the challenge and look forward to hearing more about you - submit your application today. Since this is a way to connect with us for future job openings it can take a little bit longer before you hear from us but please stay put :)

Buzz: JavaScript, JS, TypeScript, Nodejs, Node, Node.js, Angular, React, AWS, Amazon Web Services, Heroku, Backend Developer, Backend Engineer, Backend Software Developer, Frontend developer, Frontend Engineer, Software Engineer, Fullstack Developer, Full stack Engineer, Full-stack Software Engineer, MongoDB, AI, ML, Artificial intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Engineer, Data Science

Department
Tech
Locations
Stockholm
Remote status
Hybrid Remote

Title: Data Engineer / Data Scientist till Preem
Description:
Nu har du möjlighet att bli pionjär i Preems nyligen etablerade dataplattform och skapa värde för verksamheten och omvärlden genom data. Haka på deras digitala transformation och bli en viktig del i resan mot en grönare framtid. Vi söker en Data Engineer / Data Scientist med passion för problemlösning och intresse för Databricks, Machine Learning och Big Data.

Om rollen

I rollen som Data Engineer / Data Scientist kommer du få vara en del av Preems storsatsning till att höja datakvalitén och bli mer datadrivna. Du kommer ha en central roll i att utveckla och implementera initiativ kopplat till data. Arbetet rör ett framväxande funktionsområde inom företaget och det finns stort utrymme att ingå i de arkitekturella frågeställningarna och besluten.

Du kommer vara en del i ett team tillsammans med utvecklare, lösnings- och informationsarkitekter vars uppgifter är att säkerställa en kontrollerad och fungerande helhet gällande IT-arkitektur, Information Management och Masterdata Management.

Huvudsakliga arbetsuppgifter:
Bygga och underhålla den koncerngemensamma dataplattformen (Databricks i Azure)
Optimera data pipelines
Möjliggöra snabb och pålitlig dataåtkomst
Utföra avancerade analyser av data för att hitta mönster och generera insikter för att fatta bättre affärsbeslut
Etablera, utveckla och förvalta machine learning
Du blir en viktig del av Preem - en arbetsplats som präglas av välkomnande stämning, förtroende för medarbetarna och ambitionen att vara bäst i branschen när det gäller hållbarhet. Här får du frihet under ansvar och ofta chansen att vara med under hela processen - från början till slut. Ansvarstagande, nyskapande och inkluderande värderas högt på Preem och genomsyrar allt arbete. Därför är det viktigt att du delar samma uppfattning.

Rollen är en heltidstjänst till Preems huvudkontor i Stockholm. Preem har en hybrid work-model där du kan arbeta på distans hälften av din arbetstid. Du rapporterar till chefen för Digital, BI & Governance.

Är det här du?

Vi söker dig som är en passionerad problemlösare med intresse för att använda data för att lösa affärsproblem och förbättra verksamheter. Vi ser gärna att du arbetet med Azure Databricks, Machine Learning och Big Data-teknologier.

För att lyckas i rollen är det viktigt att du har god samarbetsförmåga, är initiativtagande och har ett flexibelt förhållningssätt. Vi kommer att lägga stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper.

Du har:
Erfarenhet av att jobba med Data Engineering och/eller Data Science
Goda kunskaper i programmering, särskilt i SQL och Python med tillhörande bibliotek och ramverk
God konceptuell förståelse för maskininlärning
Erfarenhet av DevOps-processer
Bekantskap med olika databaser och datalagringssystem
Akademisk examen inom datavetenskap, statistik, matematik eller liknande
Meriterande:
Erfarenhet av att arbeta tillsammans med kravställare på data för BI- och OI-rapportering
Insikt i de arkitekturella vägval som är aktuella i implementationen av en dataplattform med Lakehouse-struktur
Fördjupad förståelse av maskininlärning
Databricks och relaterade verktyg
Big Data-teknologier
MLOps och CI/CD
Rollen kräver att man kan kommunicera obehindrat i tal och skrift både på svenska och engelska.

Intresserad av att ansöka eller få veta mer?

I denna rekrytering samarbetar Preem med IDG Recruitment. Vid intresse eller frågor kontakta Moa Eriksson, Rekryteringskonsult på 070 828 36 65, moa.eriksson@idg.se eller Maria Widegren, Rekryteringskonsult 073 423 15 50, maria.widegren@idg.se

För att ansöka, vänligen skicka in ditt CV eller ansök med Linkedin.

Om Preem

Vi är Preem, Sveriges största drivmedelsbolag. Vi har en vision om att leda omvandlingen mot ett hållbart samhälle genom att bli klimatneutrala i hela värdekedjan, från utvinning av råvaror till produktion och försäljning. Senast år 2030 ska Preem producera 5 miljoner kubikmeter förnybara drivmedel, och senast 2035 ska vi vara klimatneutrala i hela värdekedjan. Preems raffinaderier räknas till de mest moderna och miljöanpassade i Europa med en raffineringskapacitet på över 18 miljoner kubikmeter per år. Vår verksamhet omfattar produktion, försäljning, distribution samt trading och varuförsörjning. Vi förädlar och säljer drivmedel, eldnings- och smörjolja samt andra produkter till företag och privatpersoner. Vi har ett rikstäckande servicenät med drygt 520 tankställen för privat- och yrkestrafik. Preem AB har drygt 1 500 anställda varav 950 arbetar vid raffinaderierna. För helåret 2020 var Preems omsättning 68,2 miljarder SEK.

Title: Forward-deployed Data Engineer
Description:
Who We Are

Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we work closely with clients to embrace a transformational approach aimed at benefiting all stakeholders—empowering organizations to grow, build sustainable competitive advantage, and drive positive societal impact.

Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives that question the status quo and spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting, technology and design, and corporate and digital ventures. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, fueled by the goal of helping our clients thrive and enabling them to make the world a better place.

Practice Area Profile

BCG GAMMA combines innovative skills in computer science, artificial intelligence (AI), statistics, and machine learning with deep industry and functional expertise. The BCG GAMMA team is comprised of world-class data scientists, software and data engineers, as well as product experts with a consulting mindset.
We specialize in creating competitive advantage for our clients through AI driven transformations. Our teams own the full analytics value-chain end to end: framing new business challenges, designing innovative algorithms, implementing and deploying scalable solutions, and enabling colleagues and clients to fully embrace AI. Our product offerings span from fully custom-build to industry specific leading edge AI software solutions.

What You'll Do

As a forward-deployed Data Engineer, you’ll be part of our rapidly growing engineering team and help build the next generation of AI solutions. You’ll have the chance to partner with clients in a variety of BCG regions and industries, and on key topics like climate change, enabling them to design, build, and deploy new and innovative solutions. Additional responsibilities will include developing and delivering thought leadership in scientific communities and papers as well as leading conferences on behalf of BCG GAMMA.
WHO YOU ARE
We are looking for talented individuals with a passion for data engineering, software development and transforming organizations into AI led innovative companies
Apply data engineering practices and standards to develop robust and maintainable solutions
Actively involved in every part of the software development life cycle
Experienced at guiding non-technical teams and consultants in best practices for large-scale data engineering
Motivated by a fast-paced, service-oriented environment and interacting directly with clients on new features for future product releases
Enjoy collaborating in teams to share software design and solution ideas
A natural problem-solver and intellectually curious across a breadth of industries and topics



What You'll Bring (Experience & Qualifications)

Master’s Degree in Computer Science or relevant field
Experience in data engineering and working with global and remote agile squads
Proficiency with analytic software programming ideally in python, C++, or SCALA
Fluency with the storage, manipulation, and management of relational, non-relational and streaming data structures, specifically SQL, Spark, and Hadoop
Proficiency with infrastructure as code principles
Experience working on AWS, Azure, or Google cloud infrastructure
NICE TO HAVE
DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD, Terraform
Understanding of parallel computing
Full stack development: GraphQL, React, JavaScript, TypeScript
Data Science and machine learning (Pandas, Scikit learn)
WORK ENVIRONMENT
Fluency in English is required as well as fluency in the local language for most locations
Ability to travel based on client and business needs. Expect 30-50%

Title: Data Engineer to Cary Group
Description:
Are you a driven data engineer with solid experience from building data platforms? Would you enjoy a dynamic work environment in a fast-growing global organization?
Cary Group comes from a long tradition of entrepreneurial family businesses with a culture that cultivates autonomy and is recognized for its sense of togetherness.
Their journey started in 1947 with Ryds Bilglas in Sweden and today they serve customers in nine European countries.
We are now looking for a data engineer to join Cary Group in Stockholm!

ABOUT THE JOB
In the role of data engineer, you will be involved in building Cary Group’s Azure cloud platform. You will integrate multiple data sources and build the data models needed for analysis. In this role, you will be an important part of the digital customer journey and you will have a close dialogue with other functions and stakeholders of the company to understand and meet their data needs.
Your primary work assignments:
Ensure reliable methods are in place to collect, integrate, clean, manage, store and prepare data for analysis.
Analyze and organize raw data.
Assess business needs and goals.
Interpret trends and patterns.

THE ROLE
Requirements:
Experience from a similar role
Experience with Azure DevOps
Previously built data pipelines or Data Factory
Experience with Data Lake
Worked with BI tools, preferably Power BI
Relevant training for the role
Speaks and writes fluent Swedish and English
You are a responsive, flexible, structured, and driven team player who thrives in a role that involves a lot of collaboration and communication with different functions of the company. You also need to be solution-oriented and analytical as well as enjoy taking initiative.
ABOUT US
Cary Group specializes in repair and replacement of vehicle glass, with an expanded offering in auto body repair. Our services extend the life of vehicles and maintain their safety features. Cary Group comes from a long heritage of entrepreneur-driven family businesses that have always cared about their customers and have had a long-term perspective on their operations. This shared heritage is what has gotten us to where we are today. It is also what guides us into our common future. Our culture is based on five pillars: simplify, empower, smarter, caring, and together. They are our values and they guide us in everything we do. Today, we are present in nine European countries where we operate through several well-known and successful brands.
Our head office is in Hammarby sjöstad in Stockholm, where we are approximately 50 co-workers.
For more information, visit https://carygroup.com/
Contact:
In this recruitment, we are collaborating with Wise IT. If you want to know more, contact the responsible recruitment consultant Sandra Åhs at Sandra.ahs@wiseit.se. Unfortunately, we cannot accept applications via email as we protect your privacy. You can read more about how we process personal data according to the GDPR in the Wise Group’s policy for the processing of personal data.
Selection is ongoing, we welcome your application!

Title: Data Engineer | Stockholm | Leading Healthcare provider
Description:
Data Engineer | Stockholm | Leading Healthcare provider
NFI - 08.11.22. AVW_1667909017
This dominating Health care provider is embarking on a journey to modernize its platforms through the use of data. Here is the opportunity for an ambitious Data Engineer to help them achieve their goal the.

The projects you work on here will take place mostly with developments in the Azure environment, in order to facilitate their move to the cloud. You will also play an important role in developing integration's and the self-built frameworks they have for data charging and testing.

Despite being part of a nationally dominating company, your team here is close-knit, allowing you to really get to know your colleagues and have a high level of collaboration. Omvärldsbevakning av teknikutvecklingen samt rådgivning och vägledning mot nästa steg i utvecklingen
Hands-on arbete nära infrastrukturen i analysmiljön

Title: Data Engineer to Vetfamily
Description:
Do you have a passion for well-structured data pipelines and want to be responsible for developing and maintaining our data warehouse?

Vimian is a global and diversified group of innovation-driven companies with a shared passion for making a positive impact through improving animal health. Together we put science, technology and our customer’s needs at the centre of everything we do to deliver effective solutions to veterinary professionals, labs and pet owners around the world.

We are looking for a self-driven, structured Data Warehouse Engineer to join our IT & BI team and lead the work in extending the Financial Data Warehouse into an insight generating business platform. We are looking for candidates with understanding of ERP systems and Financial Book Keeping and having a track record of operating system with a multitude of sources. The right candidate will find an exciting role leading a highly prioritized project within the financially stable and fast growing international Vimian Group.

What you will do:
Take over ownership of the established, well architectured and documented data warehouse platform which runs on Azure with Data factory, Synapse and powerBI.
Ensure the integrity of the dataware house architecture as you extend it with additional sources of data.
Continuously extend the pipelines as new companies are acquired and onboarded.
Jointly with the rest of the powerBI team, collaborate with Group Management, Finance, and operations to provide data analysis to answer business questions.
Ensure the DWH transforms the data into usable and presentable insight.
Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure the established data definitions match their expectations.
With us, you will be leading highly prioritized projects to spread data accessibility and usage through data pipelines across the Vimian Group.
Ensure a stable and reliable DWH that can deliver key financial data even during critical reporting periods.
Is this you?

Structured and self motivated.
Ability to maintain architecture while growing features and extending pipelines.
Bachelor or Master’s degree in Computer Science or Data science.
4+ years data engineering experience as a BI developer or software engineer.
Experience with Azure Synapse, Azure Devops, Azure Data factory powerBI. Or extensive experience with similar tools and a willingness and ability to quickly learn new tools.
Expert knowledge of SQL, Cloud Hosted Data warehouse Management.
Scripting knowledge.

Title: Algorithm Developers - Autonomous Vehicles, Computer Vision & Sensor Fusion
Description:
Personality / Commitment
Hi! We are now looking for you who are passionate about Algorithm development, Autonomous Vehicles and Computer Vision to join our team of driven professionals working with the latest technology. If you’re currently on the look-out for new challenges - we are the perfect match for you!
What we offer you:
Every employee is equally valuable in the success of ALTEN! We believe in growing together by offering opportunities, development and togetherness. ALTEN operates in several different industries, having a wide variety of assignments, coaching managers and training through ALTEN Academy, which means that it will always be possible to develop at ALTEN. Your wishes will guide your way forward.
As a consultant, you will get the genuine team feeling at your assignment but also a wonderful togetherness at ALTEN. Through our different internal networks, such as Women@ALTEN and ALTEN Sports you will get the opportunity to drive topics and activities that are close to your heart. At ALTEN, we think it's important to have a balance between work and spare time, which is why we offer three extra days off a year. We have a collective agreement and offer benefits like pension, insurances and wellness grants
Job / Skills
Your role as Algorithm Development Engineer:
The team is now looking to grow and strengthen the department with skilled Algorithm Developers towards our Autonomous Vehicles and Computer Vision customers. The projects could be both on-site and for inhouse projects.
Usually, you have a strong background within C++ and Python and have a strong interest in signal and image processing. For many roles it is meriting to have a background working with sensors or sensor data such as radar, lidar, visual or thermal but also localization.
It is a wide a very interesting field so we see that you can come from many different backgrounds and fit many different roles. Feel free to reach out to the recruitment team with any questions.
Who we are looking for:
Algorithm Developer – As an algorithm developer you usually have a strong C++ background with good knowledge in Python. You have previously worked with signal or image processing, sensors or sensor fusion in some form.
Function Developer – As Function Developer within ADAS you usually have a strong Matlab/Simulink background with knowledge within C/C++ development. You have previously worked within the automotive domain or have a strong interest in the technology area.
Data Engineer - We think you have a strong background within C++ and Python. You probably have experience of SQL or other databases. You might also have experience in maintenance of CI/CD using GitLab.
Software Architect - As an architect you come from a strong background within software development. You usually have knowledge and experience from working with safety critical real time embedded control system as well as being a technical lead and software architecture.
We handle the applications on an ongoing basis, so do not hesitate to contact us today – we believe in growing together!
About ALTEN:
ALTEN is one of Europe’s largest technology and IT consulting companies with over 45,000 employees in over 30 countries. Our engineers carry out complex and highly technical projects throughout the value chain of the most prestigious companies in all sectors, such as Automotive, Telecom, Industry, Energy, Aerospace & Defense and Life Science. In Sweden, we are over 1300 committed employees with 11 offices in 10 cities - from Lund in the south to Skellefteå in the north.
For the fourth year in a row, ALTEN has been named one of Sweden's most attractive employers by Karriärföretagen 2023, an award for employers that offer unique career and development opportunities. Welcome to read more about us at alten.se

Title: BI Developer-konsult
Description:
Vi startade Signific för att kunna lösa världens mest spännande och utmanande problem. Det gör vi genom att hjälpa organisationer och team att samla in, strukturera upp och agera på insikter från stora mängder kvantitativ data. På så sätt lär de sig snabbare om hur nytta, förändring och effekt skapas.
Signific jobbar med datadrivna, vassa och nyfikna kunder som t.ex. Detectify, Transfer Galaxy, Volvo M och SVT.
Som BI Developer-konsult på Signific har du möjlighet att jobba i uppdrag där du får vara lika delar data engineer och insiktsskapande analytiker. Och allt däremellan.
Vi vet att det ofta krävs personer som gör mer eller mindre strukturerad data redo för värdeskapande analyser. Någon som kan göra den där kopplingen mellan två olika system. Eller sätta upp det där jobbet som tar bort otaliga manuella timmar. Eller den där datamodellen som låser upp helt nya insikter om företaget. Man kan kalla det BI Developer, Analytics/Data Engineer, men viktigast är att du gillar att göra skillnad med data.
Utöver att göra skillnad i dina uppdrag är du en stor del av ett framåtlutat bolag som sätter våra anställda i fokus. Vi är ett litet, flexibelt bolag med stora ambitioner och vill ha med dig på resan dit.
Vad du kommer få göra
Vi tror på en öppen approach till lösningar på våra kunders utmaningar. Vi väljer lösning efter problem och inte vice versa. Din roll kan därför variera beroende på ditt intresse och kundernas problem.
Som BI Developer hos oss ser vi dig troligen göra några av följande saker:
Först och främst hjälpa företag skapa mer nytta av sin data
Ta komplex data till modeller och analyser som löser viktiga verksamhets- soch samhällsproblem
Bygga moderna datastackar
Sätta upp smarta, moderna och kontextspecifika lösningar på dataproblem
Lägga ihop datakällor via API:er
Driva på analys av stora datamängder
Ha en nyckelroll i att förflytta team och organisationer mot ett datadrivet arbetssätt
Få ta del av och bidra till kunskapsdelning och nyskapande kultur ihop med dina kollegor
Utvecklas åt det håll du vill
Vem vi tror du är
Vi tror på att bygga ett bolag av olika personer som på olika sätt bidrar till att vi alla trivs och lyckas. För att du ska trivas hos oss och i din roll tror vi dock att det finns några saker som du checkar av merparten av:
Som person
Ser positivt på utmaningar
Gillar att vara självgående men också att samarbeta
Nyfiken på nya teknologier och problem
Vill vara så bra som möjligt på det du gör
Du får gärna ha hobbyprojekt vid sidan av
Gillar att sälja, kunskapsdela och/eller bidra till kulturen bland dina kollegor
I din roll
Är genuint intresserad av att lösa kunders verksamhetsproblem
Har minst tre års arbetslivserfarenhet inom rollen eller liknande roller
Känner dig bekväm inom minst ett visualseringsverktyg som Tableau, Power BI eller Google Data Studio.
Toppen om du kan eller har intresse av lösningar som dbt, fivetran/stitch/airbyte
Van att jobba med API:er och databaser
Tar dig fram på SQL
Förstår vilka mått och mätpunkter som är viktiga för digitala produkter
Gillar och förstår statistik (som t.ex. A/B-tester, signfikanstester och regressionsmodellering)
Noggrann men också lösningsorienterad
Trivs att jobba i agila team och kanske också i en mer ledande roll.
Har stort intresse för Data Engineering/Science/Analytics i allmänhet
Högskoleutbildning är inget krav, men konkret arbetslivserfarenhet är det.
En spännande resa där du får vara med och påverka
Vi är ett nystartat litet bolag, med ambitioner att göra stort avtryck i våra uppdrag och på längre sikt. Vi vill skapa en samling av dom bästa inom vår nisch och bygga en stark kultur av gemenskap, ambition och kunskap. Något som gör en signifikant skillnad helt enkelt.
Hos oss får du
Utmanande uppdrag inom områden du är intresserad av
Kollegor som ser möjligheter och värdet med din kunskap inom data
Vassa kollegor som gillar att lära och läras av varandra
Konkurrenskraftiga förmåner
Inkluderande och hållbar arbetsmiljö
Vill du vara med och göra skillnad?

Title: Karolinska Universitetssjukhuset söker Scrum Master
Description:
Karolinska Universitetssjukhuset söker Scrum Master
Vill du göra skillnad på riktigt varje dag? Hos oss får du vara med och bygga framtidens vårdsystem!
Om oss
Karolinska Universitetssjukhusets uppdrag är att bedriva specialiserad och högspecialiserad sjukvård. Vår vision ”Vi ska bota och lindra imorgon det ingen kan bota och lindra idag” är vägledande när vi arbetar mot tydliga värden för patienter och samhälle och mot medicinska framsteg. En förutsättning för nästa steg inom den medicinska utvecklingen är förbättrade och moderniserade informationsstrukturer och digitalisering där vi i allt större utsträckning styr produktion och vårdleverans datadrivet och med digital information som beslutsstöd. I detta ingår data från strålkanoner, radioaktiva röntgenundersökningar, operationsdata, avancerade läkemedel och genetiska data som kan kombineras för att skapa nya behandlingar.
Karolinska har en stark IT-avdelning och tar nu steget mot att i partnerskap och på egen hand utveckla helt nya lösningar för vårdens digitala system som idag inte finns på marknaden. Det vi gör är unikt och kommer vara revolutionerande för utvecklingen inom hälso- och sjukvården och forskningen. Därför tar vi nu nästa steg mot ökad utvecklingsförmåga inom universitetssjukhuset för vår långsiktiga satsning. Vi har gott om erfarenhet och kunskap inom vårdens traditionella system men vi behöver bli fler som tänker nytt och som utmanar desamma. Ambition, leveransfokus och kreativitet värdesätts högt och vi behöver både bredd och spets och vi ser gärna att även talanger med mindre erfarenhet växer med oss. Som Scrum Master arbetar du från teknikstaben inom Karolinskas verksamhetsområde IT Utveckling och vårdinformation.
Din vardag som Scrum Master
Ditt huvudsakliga uppdrag är att leda våra teams utvecklingsuppdrag och team-ceremonier enligt Scrum-metodiken. Vi tror att du genom ditt intresse och tidigare uppdrag nu även har utvecklat en förmåga att planera för utvecklingsteam och vill stödja dessa under deras kunskapsutveckling genom att använda Scrum. Vi söker dig som kan vara Scrum Master för mer än ett utvecklingsteam och agera som agile coach för andra Scrum Masters i andra team. Eller dig som vill vara Scrum Master för ett team och i tillägg jobba med utveckling inom samma team (som till exempel Data Engineer eller BI-utvecklare).
Våra team jobbar med moderna verktyg och plattformar för hantering av stora mängder data. Vi använder tekniker som .NET, react, Java, scriptspråk, microservices, CI/CD, SQL, SSIS och Kafka.
Vi söker
Vi söker dig som genom din personlighet och tekniska kunnande har lätt för att vinna utvecklares förtroende och som genom ett involverande ledarskap naturligt bidrar till att upprätthålla en hög motivation i teamen. Du blir en viktig partner till såväl produktägare, linjechefer och enskilda teammedlemmar. Ditt fokus ligger på att stötta teamen i deras utveckling av såväl fantastiska produkter som uppbyggnad av kunskap och förmåga. Du trivs när det är full fart och gillar att söka ny kunskap.
Kvalifikationer
Krav:
Agilt arbetssätt, specifikt SCRUM
Minst 1 års erfarenhet som utvecklare
Erfarenhet av produktleveranser och release till användare
Meriterande:
Erfarenhet av test och kvalitetsarbete för mjukvara
Erfarenhet av DevOps, CI/CD
Tidigare ledarerfarenhet från något sammanhang. Inte nödvändigtvis professionellt.
Erfarenhet av Scaled agile där flera team levererar mot samma produktrelease.
Erfarenhet av BI-tekniker, analysverktyg som Tableau.
Erfarenhet av produktutveckling för vård eller annan regulatoriskt kontrollerad tillämpning
Om rekryteringsprocessen
Provanställning kan komma att tillämpas.
För att din ansökan ska vara komplett ska den innehålla:
CV
Personligt brev (frivilligt)
Utbildningsbevis
Välkommen med din ansökan!

Läs mer om rekryteringsprocessen på Karolinska på https://www.karolinska.se/jobba-hos-oss/rekrytering-pa-karolinska/

Om Karolinska Universitetssjukhuset
Vi på Karolinska Universitetssjukhuset är stolta över att vi är ett av världens främsta universitetssjukhus. Förutom vårt särskilda ansvar för den högspecialiserade vården i Stockholmsregionen är huvuduppdraget att tillsammans med Karolinska Institutet utbilda framtidens vårdanställda och bedriva världsledande forskning samtidigt som vi fortsätter vårt arbete med att utveckla vården för patientens bästa. Vi arbetar inom en rad olika områden och professioner.

Vår vision - Vi ska bota och lindra imorgon det ingen kan bota och lindra idag.

Läs gärna mer om oss på www.karolinska.se och följ oss på sociala medier!
Att söka jobb i Region Stockholm
Vi eftersträvar jämställdhet och jämlikhet på vår arbetsplats och ser gärna sökande med olika bakgrund och förutsättningar.
Vi tar endast emot ansökningar via detta system. Ansök genom att klicka på knappen ”Ansök”. Ansökningar per brev eller e-post beaktas inte. Vi undanber oss direktkontakt med bemannings- och rekryteringsföretag samt säljare av ytterligare jobbannonser.
Vårt rekryteringssystem kan inte hantera anonyma ansökningar eller sökande med skyddade personuppgifter. Om du har skyddade personuppgifter ber vi dig att kontakta den kontaktpersonen som finns angiven i annonsen. Din ansökan kommer då att hanteras utanför rekryteringssystemet. Du bör även vara försiktig med vilken information du lämnar i din ansökan och endast ta med information som är relevant för den aktuella befattningen.
Region Stockholm ansvarar för hälso- och sjukvård, kollektivtrafik, regional utveckling och bidrar till kulturlivet. Varje dag, dygnet runt. I landets snabbaste växande region. Tillsammans skapar vi Europas attraktivaste storstadsregion.

Title: Public Safety - Data Engineer - Stockholm
Description:
Public Safety - Data Engineer - Stockholm
NFI - 14.12.2022 avw_1671012388
Do you feel like your work is having a real-life impact on the world around you? If not perhaps its time to consider a move to a position more fulfilling. I'm working with a client whose mission is to increase the security of Sweden.

Whether there is a threat to life, property or the surrounding environment this organisation works to ensure that safety is maintained. This is through the use of alarms, from this accident and recovery responses are coordinated to ensure that effective help is given. This company works all day and every day of the year to make sure that this protection is solid, as such you'll be part of a organisation dedicated to the safety of Sweden and one that is making a real impact.

Your role here as a Data Engineer will involve migrating reports to Power BI and process large data sets, analysis from this will be key for improving their services and as such public safety. Further information gathered from here is used for research purposes and thus helping municipalities hospitals and universities.

In this role you will be collaborating with various departments to understand and improve data collection. You will be building and maintaining data pipelines, helping the migration to Power BI and ensuring that data handling meets national security regulations.

An ideal candidate will have…

Experience working with Cloud based technologies
Experience with data collecting, storage and modelling
Knowledge of databases (SQL)

Bonus if you…

Have experience working with Power BI, Qlik or Tableau

What can they offer you?

Being part of this company allows you to work with the most recent technology but also experience a position where your work is having an impact on real life events and genuinely helping people.
You'll be given a lot of responsibility here, being in a close-knit team you will have the opportunity to rally shape the data platform and the wider business
Work with a mix of colleagues from junior to expert level - here there is a really strong culture of sharing ideas and support.

They're looking for a flexible individual who shares their dynamic way of thinking, here you'll be granted and expected to bring your ideas forward for the business and have a large impact in the direction of the business.

If this sounds like an interesting opportunity that you want to learn more about then let's organise a time to discuss this and other roles we have in more detail.

Email: a.wingfield@nigelfrank.com

Title: Work Remotely Within Europe | Excellent Work-Life Balance
Description:
Work Remotely Within Europe | Excellent Work-Life Balance
NFI - 24.11.2022_1667560094
This company recognises the growing market demand for data-driven solutions and wants you to be part of their team that will help their clients generate value from their data. Owed to the immense success of this company they are seeking to expand their ranks to meet their client base's growing needs.

Here you'll be joining a direct subsidiary of a larger global group, and although only new to the market, this Gothenburg-based company has the fresh start-up feel with the experience associated with a well-established market family.

Owed to its success this company is looking to grow its team with any promising candidates whatever your background and skill. Whether you're a Business analyst, Data Engineer, or Data Scientist, if you think you would be a good fit then reach out!

Don't want to be restricted to one city? Not located within Sweden? Not a problem, as a fully remote opportunity this role allows you to work from anywhere in Europe, provided it's within a one-hour time difference.
However, if you enjoy the office environment this organisation has offices across Sweden.


For this role a successful candidate will have:

Significant experience in data and BI with an understanding of data requirements
Experience building dashboards and visualisations (Qlik or Power BI)
Experience working with cloud solutions: Azure, AWS, or GCP
Experience working with customers and end users with the ability to understand their needs.

This company prides itself on its excellent work-life balance and its well-cultivated work culture. As such they're looking to add an individual who at a personal level is positive and energetic.


What can they offer you?

Genuinely happy workplace: priding itself on more than just a workplace, this company has earned awards for employee satisfaction across Sweden.
Flexible salary package, you get choice of what you would like to take as salary, pension or other perks. Which are open to discussion depending on your preferences.
Opportunity to work with big clients and across all industries, here you have the unparalleled experience to expand your knowledge and interact with the biggest and best.
Fast-growing company, rapidly expanding and seeking to fulfil this through ambitious growth plans.
Fully remote opportunity
Great pipeline for sales/ customers - it's a large organisation on the stock market and has a tremendous pipeline



Do you think you could be a good fit for this company? Lets arrange a time to call to go through this in more detail and the other positions we have currently available.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.

For further information see www.babyshop.com

ABOUT THE POSITION

Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO

Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE

You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...

Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE

The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.

Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!

Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Analytics Engineer
Description:
Build Measure Learn Sweden is looking to expand with a Analytics Engineer to join a team at one of our customers. We are a data analytics & engineering consulting company that is expanding to meet market demand (assignments at clients) and to achieve our mission of playing an impactful part in helping companies in Sweden on their journey to become data-driven.
Are you skilled at data engineering and feel that it is time to shift context to continue your growth? Would you like colleagues that are best-in-class and humble about it? We will find a great match between you and assignment where both you and the client benefit. Our clients are in need of help in having data guide their decisions, democratizing data and using data to power everything.
We seek you that love everything about data. You love solving complex data processing problems, building large-scale batch and real-time data pipelines and designing high quality data sets. You are knowledgable and passionate about building and improving and building data platforms that power reliable and impactful data products. You are data-centric and can likely morph between a Data Engineer and Data Scientist. You want to develop your career at a growing company and work with a massive amount of data-points.
WHAT YOU’LL DO
Solve complex data processing problems for clients, making an impact across unlimited domains and industries (digital products, banking, insurance, finance, health, e-commerce, marketing, etc.)
Create new datasets for analytics capabilities
Maintain data warehouse and associated pipelines which process large amounts of data per day
Optimize data delivery and re-design infrastructure for greater scalability
Build analytics tools to provide insights into data health and accuracy
Maintain and improve data catalogs
Collaborate with stakeholders to collect business requirements and define successful analytics outcomes
Advocate for data quality, data governance, and data product thinking
Raise our customers technical excellence with clean code, thoughtful pull request reviews and mentoring others

WHO YOU ARE
3 - 7 years of experience of demonstrable experience building and maintaining large data warehouses
Demonstrated ability to design, build and maintain complex data services
Proficient at building datasets that are accurate and easy to understand and consume
Spark in Scala and/or Python
SQL and Relational Databases
Ability to be committed to the end result and help others gets there
You write code daily (Python or Scala)
Enjoy agile development and fluent in continuous Integration and delivery using Git
Fast learner, self-starter and intellectually curious
Fluent in English
Willing to learn, or already know, basic Swedish

IDEALLY, YOU WILL HAVE
Experience shaping and evolving data architecture
Knowledge of one or more business domains
Based near Stockholm or Gothenburg (or willing to relocate to Gothenburg or Stockholm)

Bonus points for:
Community involvement with open source contributions
Experience building data and analytics organizations
Knowledge of advanced statistical analysis techniques
Familiar or skilled with machine learning

WHY JOIN US?
Interesting and forward-looking assignments within fintechs, e-commerce companies and digital startups / scale-ups
Collaborative, transparent, creative and fun loving culture which you will be involved in shaping
Opportunities for personal and professional growth
Investment in your competence development in latest skills & technologies
An international team (including our partner network) ~6 nationalities so far
Competitive salary
Learning & sharing environment - colleagues skilled in their areas and that enjoy knowledge sharing
Have a mid/long term plan of becoming a freelancer? We'd like to be a part of that and help you towards that goal.
Company parties & team activities
Opportunities to have global impact with your work

How to apply:
If you fit the description above, we’d love to hear from you! Email us at: jobs@buildmeasurelearn.se
We’re looking forward to your application!
Öppen för alla
Vi fokuserar på din kompetens, inte dina övriga förutsättningar. Vi är öppna för att anpassa rollen eller arbetsplatsen efter dina behov.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
At Keolis we move people from A to B with the help of advanced technical solutions within the public transport sector. Do you want to be part of and contribute to an important aspect of peoples everyday lif? And have a passion for data and thrive in a company that works towards a sustainable future?
About the role
As a Data Engineer at Keolis, you will have a key role in our tech department and the development of our new Data team. We have just started building our data warehouse and data lake and we now have an execiting journey ahead of us, where you will set the roadmaps for how we will work with data at Keolis. You will be an important leader and a valuable support between both IT and the business to identify the need for data and our way towards a modern data driven organization. As a Data Engineer you will ensure the quality and valuate our data sources and be a part of migrating data to Azure.
As the work with advanced data analysis is in the start-up phase, you would be able to use all your experience and ideas to help us establish this new department. In the role of Data Engineer, you are responsible for building the analysis environments that will be used for machine learning and advanced analysis. You set up ETL processes, build our Data Lake and and identify our data sources. You will also work with our Data Goverence and Data modelling. Our data comes from several different business areas, everything from internal systems to live stream data from our buses. As the team's capabilities grow, so will the applications and new data sources become relevant.
Who are you?
To succeed in this role you have to work independently but appreciate being surrounded by knowledgeable colleagues and have an extraordinary ability to work together. We also believe that you are used to working with data in a Microsoft environment and have experience of retrieving data from different systems. You are also communicatively skilled and have an easy time switching between a holistic and a detailed perspective.
To succeed in this role we see that you have:
A few years' relevant work experience in a similar role
Experience of working with Microsoft products such as Azure, Azure synapse.
Experience of workning with cloud platforms.
Experience of programming languages such as R, Pyhton and
Experience of SQL databases.
Relevant higher education.
Interest and drive to develop both organizations and working methods.
Excellent ability to express yourself in English and preferally Swedish as well.
To work at Keolis
We offer you a thriving and business-oriented industry. Keolis is a global company where you will work for Keolis Sweden. We operate traffic over big parts of Sweden, currently in Dalarna, Karlstad, Uppsala, Gothenburg and Stockholm. In order for us to be able to grow, we need, among other things be able to deliver our services with higher efficiency and quality than our competitors.
As an employeer It is important to us to give you the best conditions for you to both deliver results and at the same time feel good and thrive in your role. You as an employee will receive an individually designed introductory program to give you a flying start.
We offer an exciting work environment characterized by ethnic and cultural diversity where the climate is open and we respect each other. At Keolis, you have good opportunities to combine your professional life with private life and we work actively to promote the development of our staff and grow within the company.

Contact
For questions about the recruitment process, please contact Lina Sylvén who is responsible for this recruitment, email address lina.sylven@keolis.se
For union questions contact:
Klas Wallin, representantive for Unionen at 070-602 67 74 / klas.wallin@keolis.se
Michael Lindqvist, Akademikerföreningen at 072-515 18 60 / michael.lindqvist@keolis.se

Application
Our recruitment takes place on an ongoing basis, we therefore ask you to submit your application in the form of a CV as soon as possible. You do not need to write a personal letter, but we think it is better to get to know each other by talking to each other. The selection is based on your previous experiences and on your inherent personal circumstances. We will therefore take the help of work psychological test tools from Alva Labs. The position may be filled before the application period expires. A warm welcome with your application!

Title: Senior Software Developer (Data Engineering)
Description:
EnginZyme is a Swedish venture-backed startup building a new, sustainable way to produce the building blocks of the world — the billion tonnes of plastics, nylons, rubbers, and all the other things that we touch on a day to day basis. Founded in 2014 in Stockholm, Sweden, we're funded by well-known investors, have been recognised as Technology Pioneer by the World Economic Forum, and we are on a mission to transform one of the world's largest industries. We have just raised €22M in Series B funding and are now expanding our data engineering team, which is where you come in.

In our RnD labs we process hundreds of samples daily and each one of them has plenty of metadata associated to the design, simulation, execution and analysis of experiments. This data stream constitutes our main knowledge base and we are constantly improving our data pipelines in our Laboratory Information Management System (LIMS) far beyond "just storing data in the cloud".

We need your help to augment our RnD team's capacity to make smart and informed decisions and simplify experiment management by providing tools to handle each sample's digital twin. As a data engineer you will deep-dive into our database to develop and maintain scientific data entry schemas, but you will also create researcher-friendly data pipelines bridging the robustness of structured data to everyday lab activities. You will work to integrate our LIMS with our own robots and instruments, responsibly testing and deploying internal tools and assisting researchers to seamlessly adopt them.

What you’ll do
You will work with a small group of software developers and automation engineers supporting the RnD Automation and Data Management infrastructure

Key tasks and responsibilities are:
Design, develop and maintain data pipelines to capture experimental data.
Update databases architectures to support new laboratory workflows.
Improve data quality via automated validation, curation and labeling services.
Contribute to our private python libraries to abstract database ETL operations into our R&D specific semantics.
Contribute to the business logic of our in house No Code data I/O webapps.
Deployment and maintenance of databases and services in our cloud infrastructure.

You will deep dive into our software stack, including Python (MyPy), Pydantic, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Celery/Redis, PostgreSQL, Gitlab CI/CD, DynamoDB, S3 and multiple other AWS services.
We have offices in Stockholm, Sweden and it would of course be great if you lived nearby, but it is also possible to work from home elsewhere in Europe.

What we can offer you

The opportunity to be part of something big and important:
Getting to advance state-of-the-art technology
To work with world-class researchers on problems at the frontier of the field
Competitive salary and equity in the company
Start-up mentality. No red tape, lots of responsibility and ownership
A friendly, very multi-cultural, tight-knit group employing 52 people from 24 different countries
An environment where you’re free — and expected — to continuously learn and grow
One of the best cities in the world to live and work, and we offer relocation support and help you get set up. But don't take our word for the quality of life in Stockholm — instead just listen to this guy for five minutes: https://youtu.be/CAkdWUjdJyA

Who you are
We’re looking for people who share our passion for problem-solving with no toolkit boundaries. You are an experienced software developer that thrives seeing other people using the tools you have helped to craft and deeply cares about data consistency and accessibility . You have build well documented REST API's and you have contributed with code to larger projects, so you are used to writing clear, maintainable and testable code.
In terms of personal qualities, we’re looking for someone who is passionate about their work and who wants to push boundaries. And, not least, who is also a friendly, cooperative person. If this describes you, you’ll fit in with the rest of the team!

Title: Senior Data Engineer to Product Master Data Management at SEB
Description:
Categories
Data & IT, Technology
31 January 2023
Location
Stockholm
Are you a collaborative, proactive & curious Senior Data engineer then below is an interesting position for you!

We are looking for a Senior data engineer that has a genuine interest in building powerful data pipelines and is passionate about clean code. You will be working in building SEB’s Product Master Data Platform. We manage the bank’s common Products catalogue and ensure that product- and product arrangement is made available in key banking initiatives such as digitalizing customer journeys and know your customer (KYC) processes. You together with team will take an end-2-end responsibility for our cross-platform for product master data.
The data published by Master Data Platform is used by the bank’s internal users for example: Pension & Insurance, FICC & Equities, Trading, Mortgage Loan, Private Loan, AML & holding Control and many more.
We use the following technologies:
Spring Boot, Spring Batch, Kafka, Java 17, Maven, Microsoft SQL Server, Data Lake Hadoop, Angular, OpenShift, Splunk, Junit, Mockito, REST-API, Swagger, Sonar, GitHub Actions etc.

What you will be doing:
Develop powerful data pipelines that efficiently process large volumes of product master data, by participating in all the phases of development i.e. implementation architecture, requirement collection, coding & testing etc.
Enable product- and product arrangement workflows that expose performant query interfaces and offer easy-to-use integration hooks.
Build features to tune processing pipeline and indexing depending on needs and workloads
Build solutions by using TDD and code reviews
Encourage innovation and love working with modern and agile ways of working
In practice this means that you will:
Help in formulating the implementation roadmap that meets the solution architecture.
Ability to take initiative and ownership in a fast-paced environment
Drive change and is used to work independently, in a group and taking own initiatives
The position is in Stockholm, Arenastaden and with the possibility to work two days from home.
Who are we looking for?

Relevant degree and industry experience in building complex data pipeline
Have some experience from DevOps maturity models and CI/CD
Experience with data processing frameworks (Kafka, IBM MQ etc)
Experience with different data lakes or warehouses
Experience with containerization and other modern software development paradigms.
Previous experience in the financial industry is an advantage.
Don’t meet every single requirement? If you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.
Ready to join?
Since we select candidates continuously, feel free to send in your application today, but no later than 2023-01-31. Due to end-of-year holidays we will initiate selection process in full after mid-January.
If you have questions about the position, please contact Shankar Gautam, +46 70 762 12 92
SEB Sweden has a redeployment responsibility, why this position might be covered by internal redeployment

Welcome to a community of tech-savvy and passionate employees from all corners of the world. SEB is in fact one of the largest IT employers in the Nordics. Together we future proof a world of financial flows by exploring and implementing modern digital architecture and state-of-the-art technology. We are driven by collaboration, insight, and friendship. But also, a desire to change and improve. All in all, it creates a balance - where life and a stable yet exciting job can co-exist. If you want to shape tomorrow's bank - continue reading and apply today.

Title: Biometria söker systemutvecklare till vårt team inom Business Intelligence
Description:
Biometria är en medlemsägd och central aktör inom svensk skogsnäring. Vi mäter det virke som flödar mellan skog och industri och som opartisk säkerställer vi att Sveriges skogsägare är trygga i sina virkesaffärer. Uppdraget är att stödja och utveckla virkeshandel, logistik och produktion på virkesmarknaden. Biometria erbjuder även tjänster för digitalisering och automatisering av virkesflödet och virkesaffärer, och vi har ett långsiktigt samarbete med forskningsinstitut och universitet. Genom vårt arbete verkar vi som ett informationsnav inom skogsnäringen och erbjuder en plattform med standardiserad och kvalitetssäkrad information som vi själva och andra aktörer kan bygga nya moderna tjänster på. Totalt är vi 850 anställda med verksamhet i hela Sverige, vårt huvudkontor ligger i Uppsala.
Vill du bidra till en digital revolution i skogens värdekedjor?
Inom Biometria driver vi den digitala utvecklingen för hela skogsnäringen. Vi skapar möjligheter inom digitalisering och innovation där vi testar ny teknologi. Biometria ligger i framkant avseende på både teknik och arbetssätt, bland annat genom att automatisera processen med hjälp av machine learning och AI.
Vi söker systemutvecklare till vårt team inom Business Intelligence (BI)
Vi letar efter dig som har ett passionerat intresse för ditt yrke, som gillar att lösa kluriga utmaningar och vill jobba med teknik som ligger i framkant. Har du en gedigen och mångårig erfarenhet eller är du nyutexaminerad och kunskapstörstig och vill lära dig? Vi värdesätter olikheterna i erfarenheter, kunskap och synsätt och ser det som viktiga byggklossar i en lärande organisation.
Biometria hanterar stora mängder data som ägs av våra kunder, i Biometrias data warehouse. I nuläget visualiserar vi datat till stor del i rapporter, som Biometrias kunder använder. Behovet av analyser kan komma att ändras med framtiden, där prognostisering blir alltmer viktigt för branschen.
Ditt ansvar och dina arbetsuppgifter
Du ingår i vårt utvecklingsteam där dina arbetsuppgifter är att utveckla de lösningar som Microsoft plattform Power BI möjliggör. Systemutvecklingen sker både i backend- och frontendmiljö och vi arbetar i en microservices-arkitektur i Azure. Vi går mot att bli en DevOps-organisation där teamen tar ett helhetsansvar över våra produkter.
I backend jobbar vi med ett antal ramverk och programspråk såsom Azure SQL server, Blobstorage, .NET Core, Azure Keyvault, Azure Functions, BIML (Business Intelligence Markup Language). Datat struktureras med datamodellen data vault i olika relationsdatabaser och laddar tabulärer för vidare bearbetning och visualisering i frontend.
I frontend jobbar vi med ett antal ramverk och programspråk såsom Azure SQL server, SSAS (SQL Server Analysis Services), tabulärmodeller, DAX, SSIS (SQL Server Integration Services), External tables, Data Factory, Azure Analytics, BIML, Star Schema (fakta och dimensionstabeller), Azure AD, Power BI. Dataskiss skapas i ett Star Schema och utifrån strukturerat data i tabulärer skapas en eller flera rapporter, eller andra typer av analyser i Power BI.
Som systemutvecklare har du ansvar för att stötta teamet i tekniska problemlösningar med utgångspunkt från slutanvändarens behov. Du har täta kontakter med andra systemutvecklare, användbarhetsexperter, IT-arkitekter, testare, verksamhetsutvecklare samt produktägare
Vem är du?
Du gillar statistik och matematik, har högskoleutbildning eller relevant IT-utbildning inom området, i rollerna Data engineer, Data analyst eller Data scientist. Du är orädd, nyfiken och gillar utmaningar. Du trivs med att vara del av ett team och har lätt för att samarbeta, men är också självgående och drivande inom ditt område. Du gillar att jobba i ett öppet samarbetsklimat i en grupp som har ett helhetsansvar för de produkter som finns inom produktområdet. Du gillar att hantera och strukturera stora datamängder samt modellera och ta fram bra analysverktyg för kunden.
Vi ser gärna att du kan tänka utanför ramarna och vill ligga i framkant med de nyaste teknikerna inom Microsoft Power BI och vill utvecklas i takt med nya tekniksprång.
Vårt erbjudande
Våra värderingar är ledord för vårt förhållningssätt och våra värdeord är pålitliga, opartiska, engagerade och tillsammans. Alla ska ha utrymme för att kunna utföra sitt uppdrag, att våga testa och även ta hjälp av varandra för att lyckas. Det ska kännas tryggt och roligt att komma till jobbet. Vi stöttar varandra och ser varandra som kollegor och medmänniskor.
Vi erbjuder dig ett självständigt arbete med möjlighet att arbeta på distans.
Vi erbjuder också privat sjukvårdsförsäkring samt att vi har flera fritidsboenden att låna/hyra och självklart erbjuder vi våra anställda friskvårdsbidrag.
Biometria verkar för att skapa en attraktiv arbetsplats med öppenhet och ett tillåtande klimat. Varje medarbetares individuella förutsättningar och kompetens tas tillvara – det är bra att vi är olika!
Vid en anställning skapar vi en plan för dig för att du ska få en så bra introduktion som möjligt till vår tekniska plattform och organisation.
Din ansökan
Vänligen skicka in din ansökan genom länken nedan. Din ansökan skall innehålla en presentation av dig själv och vad som lockar med tjänsten samt en meritförteckning/CV.
Information om anställningen
Löne- och anställningsvillkor: Enligt gällande kollektivavtal
Tillträde: Enligt överenskommelse
Anställningsform: Tillsvidare
Anställningens omfattning: Heltid
Upplysningar om anställningen lämnas av: Produktområdeschef för Produktion och BI, Ted Danielsson, 010-228 50 47
Fackliga representanter: Jens Nordenberg, Akademikerföreningen 010-228 51 16 och Marie Söder, Unionen 010-228 5139
Välkommen att skicka in din ansökan senast den 2023-02-20
Vi har gjort vårt medieval för rekrytering och undanber oss erbjudanden om rekryterings- och annonseringshjälp.
Genom din ansökan samtycker du till att Biometria får nyttja dina personuppgifter i syfte att genomföra rekryteringsarbete kopplat till denna tjänst i enlighet med Dataskyddsförordningen GDPR. Vänligen läs mer på Integritetsskyddsmyndigheten. (imy.se)

Title: Data Warehouse Engineer till VX Fiber i Umeå
Description:
Om företaget
VX Fiber är en internationell fiberoperatör – en specialist inom digital infrastruktur. VX Fiber bygger och driver öppna accessnät över hela världen. Bolaget har sitt ursprung i Sverige men har kontor på flera platser i Europa. Vill du arbeta med ny, fräsch teknik i en internationell verksamhet med en stor möjlighet att växa, både som person och i din yrkesroll? Är du driven och tycker om att arbeta med engagerade kollegor och trivs med frihet under ansvar? Till utvecklingsteamet i Umeå söker vi nu en driven och engagerad Data Warehouse Engineer. Välkommen med din ansökan!
Nivån på teknisk kompetens i bolaget är mycket hög och för rätt individer erbjuds möjligheter till långsiktig karriärutveckling. Vi drivs av ny teknik och innovation och prioriterar att skapa nytt i stället för att nöja oss med det invanda. Vi verkar på en internationell marknad där vi vill göra både spännande och intressanta saker. I våra affärer ingår vi partnerskap med lokala myndigheter, fastighetsägare, investerare, markägare och samhällen när vi tillsammans bygger och driver fibernät och automatiserade nätverks- och kundsystem för öppna nät. Vi samarbetar med flera tjänsteleverantörer och operatörer för att erbjuda en mängd olika produkter och tjänster direkt till abonnenten via en självförsörjande webbaserad portal.
Detta förutsätter ett långsiktigt och hållbart tänk kring våra affärer där du kommer känna att du bidrar med verklig nytta både internt och externt.
Team VX Dev
Du kommer ingå i teamet VX Dev som idag finns i Umeå, Stockholm och Milano. Vi arbetar med den senaste teknologin och levererar vår mjukvara i en så kallad service-mesh på en hybrid-moln plattform med hjälp av Nomad, Vault och Consul. Vi jobbar ständigt med att utvecklas och bli bättre genom att arbeta med metodiker såsom Lean - Agile.
Vi är snabbfotade och premierar handling före passivitet där osäkerhet för vilken som är den bästa idén sällan står i vägen för oss. Genom att vara ödmjuka, pragmatiska och jobba med reflektion blir vi ständigt bättre och bättre.
Dina arbetsuppgifter
I rollen som Data Engineer hos oss kommer du huvudsakligen arbeta med att designa, utveckla och driva implementation och förbättringsarbetet kring vårt Data Warehouse.
Du kommer få arbeta med en modern platform
Du kommer vara i nära samarbete med våra utvecklare som både kollega och kravställare.
Du kommer skapa rapporter i Power BI
Du kommer arbeta med Azure Data factory för att hämta in data från våra mikrotjänster till vår Azure SQL Server. Insamling sker via databas (sql, mongo m.fl) men även via REST och vårt nya GraphQL api.
Vidare kommer du i denna nya roll se till att strukturera upp datainsamlingen och även bidra till utvecklingen av vår plattform för att förbättra våra analys- och rapportbehov.
Du ingår i ett team med end-to-end ansvar där arkitektur och systemdesign är en viktig del av arbetet och du kommer få ta dig an nya spännande arbetsuppgifter tillsammans med väldigt engagerade och kompetenta kollegor som finns i både Umeå, Stockholm och Milano.
Din profil
Du har jobbat med Data Warehouse tidigare och är redo för nya utmaningar i ett startup företag med stora visioner. Vårt Data Warehouse är modellerat enligt Kimballs Principer med stjärn-schema och uppbyggt av dimensions- och faktatabeller.
Vi tror att du har tidigare erfarenhet av databasmodellering och gärna flerårig erfarenhet av SQL, samt så har du jobbat tidigare med Linux och Windows system. Erfarenhet av dataanalys och Bi-rapporter är meriterande. Det är även meriterande om du har jobbat inom Telekombranschen men det är inget krav.
Din utbildningsbakgrund är inte det viktigaste utan det vi värderar högst är att du är duktig, driven, pragmatiskt och ser det som självklart att använda de verktyg och metoder är lämpligast i sammanhanget. Vidare så behärskar du engelska och svenska obehindrat i både tal och skrift. Som person trivs du i ett arbetsklimat där du får möjligheten att arbeta med frihet under ansvar och flexibla arbetstider. Du motiveras av att lära dig nya saker, att utmana dig sig själv samt vågar testa och tänka nytt. Du är pragmatisk och väljer att fokusera på lösningar i stället för problem.
Vidare trivs du med att jobba i ett riktigt vasst team – som utmanar och stöttar varandra och du är en problemlösare med ett affärsmässigt tänk.
an
I denna rekrytering samarbetar vi med Clockwork Rekrytering och Bemanning. För mer information är du varmt välkommen att kontakta Jennifer Åström Gustafsson på 0733-51 27. Vi arbetar med rekryteringsprocessen löpande, så ansök så snart som möjligt, dock senast den 31 januari via www.clockworkpeople.se.

Title: Join QRIOS IT! It will be fun!
Description:

Join QRIOS IT

Qrios IT is growing and we are looking for people for assignments within the following areas:

Software/System Development (Frontend, Backend, Fullstack)

DevOps Engineering
Architectecting: Solution/Cloud/Enterprise
