Machine Learning, AI, Big Data
Team Lead, Engineering Manager, Scrum Masters
For this position we require that you have documented work experience in Cloud. For example Azure, AWS or GCP.

About the organisation
The most important thing we have is our people
At QRIOS, we know that the most important thing we have is our people. From the first contact in our recruitment process to how we internally tailor our approach, to promote and enable continuous learning. You will have the opportunity to choose from a variety of challenging assignments and can feel confident that your colleagues at QRIOS have a very high level of technical expertise. We’re not interested in being just another consultancy firm – we’re interested in being the best at what we do.

Curious and always wanting to develop. QRIOS MINDS GO FURTHER.

People first at QRIOS
There are only 24 hours in a day, even though our lives sometimes requires twice that amount. At QRIOS you will have the opportunity to train, take new certificates, participate in fun events and after-work activities, give lectures, do things you find really fun and challenging and much more.
If you want.

It’s up to you. We give you the opportunities, and you decide what suits you and your life.

Title: Data Engineer till SGDS Gruppen
Description:
SGDS Gruppen AB är ett nybildat bolag som innefattar säljbolagen Dahl, Optimera, Bevego, Kakelspecialisten och Konradssons Kakel. Tillsammans omsätter vi drygt 17 miljarder, har över 170 etableringar och är nästan 3000 medarbetare. Vi har Sveriges bredaste sortiment av produkter och tjänster inom området bygg och installation. Våra säljande bolag fokuserar på att driva och utveckla affärer med personal inom sälj, butik, kategori och prefab. I det nybildade bolaget SGDS Gruppen samlar vi alla affärsstödjande funktioner som exempelvis ekonomi, logistik samt digitalt och IT.
Inom SGDS Gruppen är vi mitt uppe i en digitaliseringsresa. Som del i detta initiativ satsar vi på att bli mer datadrivna. Vi har av den anledningen börjat bygga en ny dataplattform för alla bolag inom SGDS Gruppen. Dataplattformen består bland annat av Data Lake, Data Warehouse (DWH) och Master data Management (MDM). Vi bygger våra tjänster på moderna molnteknologier i Microsoft Azure.
DIN VARDAG HOS OSS
I din roll som Data Engineer kommer du bland annat:
Skapa informationsmodeller för SGDS verksamhetsområden
Bygga DataWareHouse mha moderna molntjänster i Azure
Skapa och vidareutveckla moderna analysmetoder såsom AI, prediktiv analys, etc.
Samarbeta med BI analytiker för att få fram rapportdatabaser som kan utgöra datakälla för våra Power-BI rapporter
Skapa stöd för att bygga dashboards och rapporter på strömmande data
Göra utredningar och förstudier för att skapa beslutsunderlag för lösningar av SGDS IT-system
Du kommer att vara en viktig spelare i att göra SGDS gruppen till ett mer datadrivet företag och en nyckelperson för att etablera en gemensam plattform kring data och analytics.
VI TROR ATT VÅR NYA KOLLEGA HAR:
Tidigare erfarenhet av att implementera datalager och BI.
Erfarenhet av att designa och implementera BI lösningar samt har du goda tekniska kunskaper kring
databaser samt stor vana av att skapa datamodeller och ETL operationer.
Erfarenhet av att jobba med cloudtjänster, Azure och/eller AWS
Extra god kompetens kring Microsoft SQL Server och Power BI.
Stort intresse av programmering och att lösa tekniska problem
Intresset av att förstå verksamheten och brinner för att hitta sätt att förbättra.
Eftergymnasial utbildning, gärna som ingenjör.
DU ÄR VARMT VÄLKOMMEN
Vi vill att samtliga medarbetare ska trivas, må bra och ha kul på jobbet. Vi har en stark tro på att våra medarbetare är avgörande i vår framgång och vi är måna om att samtliga medarbetare ska kunna växa och göra karriär hos oss. Några av våra förmåner är pensionsavtal enligt ITP, Rikskortet, friskvårdsbidrag, regelbundna hälsokontroller samt rabatter i alla SGDS butiker.
ANSÖKAN
SGDS-Gruppen samarbetar med Wise IT i denna rekrytering och du är varmt välkommen att kontakta vår rekryterare Josefine Lindborg vid frågor. Ansök redan idag via vårt webbformulär då ansökningar behandlas löpande (inga ansökningar via mejl pga GDPR). Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning.

Title: Senior Data Architect
Description:
Why Avaus?
We are the leading marketing and sales transformation partner in the Nordics! We are 120 colleagues located at our offices in Helsinki, Stockholm, Munich, Milan and Gdansk. As a company, we have more than 15 years of experience in data-driven marketing and sales in large organizations across B2C & B2B industries.

Our vision is to become the leading actionable marketing data-asset provider in Europe by 2025. We believe that to survive, companies need to invest heavily in capabilities related to intelligence & AI, customer experience, personalisation and change management. Our mission is to foster customer-centric companies equipped to grow and face the future. Our own future growth is heavily driven by activating data and analytics for our clients.

The Team
The market is shifting faster than ever and to keep up, companies need to invest in their data capabilities to deliver relevant and tailored content and information fit to your and your customers’ needs. This is where we come in as engineers. By utilizing the latest, leading cloud technologies combined with machine learning, we build scalable, future proof data solutions, to achieve this goal.

As a new member of our Data Engineering team, your responsibilities involve design and development of varieties of data processing solutions. The team provides the technical backbone needed for a data-driven and personalized customer experience. At Avaus you will find a collaborative environment with lots of personal responsibility and freedom where your problem solving abilities and eagerness to learn new technologies will flourish. Here you will take ownership and drive conversations and tasks on your own initiative. We are a social crew and enjoy working closely together and learning from one another.

The role
As a Data Engineer you will work in multidisciplinary client teams. You will work in an Agile environment where you have a client-facing role and work in close collaboration with our clients' business and technical stakeholders. You will use your patented passion to capture and understand the requirements of complex data solutions. Effectiveness in a collaborative environment and valuing teamwork is one of the keys to this role.You will most likely be doing some of these things also:

Be part of feature development, from planning all the way through to test and delivery
Working closely together with our data science team in delivering machine learning solutions by using the latest in technology
Be part of Avaus internal development initiatives, where we set new standards in how we deliver to our clients
Security and privacy measures
Who are you?
We're looking for a person with a passion for technology and data. You understand the need for and importance of continuous delivery and what's required. You have prioritizing elegance and simplicity when writing code. People describe you as a team-player and you have the ability to create valuable relationships. You have a strong sense of ownership and want to be part of our journey! Beside your personality, we would also like you to have:

Academic Bachelor's degree, e.g computer science, technology or similar
Extensive experience in building and designing customer data solutions on one of the three big cloud platforms. E.g GCP, AWS or Azure, GCP in particular
Expert in SQL and data modelling
Extensive experience of concepts and building continuous integration/deployment solutions and Infrastructure as code
Extensive experience with the concept of microservices and how to build such architectures
Experience in implementing security and privacy best practices, knowledge in how to deliver GDPR-compliant solutions
Expert in one or more programming languages like Python or Java
Experience in consulting
Experience in containers and container-based solutions
Fluent in English
Practical information:
This is a permanent position with a 6 months’ probation period, based at our Stockholm office at Katarinavägen 17. Starting date as soon as possible or by agreement. We offer a hybrid remote workplace and you will report to Team Lead, Anthon Ytterell.

Already feel like one of us? Send your applications in English as soon as possible, but no later than 2023-02-28. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Anthon. Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
In a world where product size labels are unreliable, Volumental is the footwear industry's leading FitTech™ company, using 3D scans and a one-of-a-kind, AI-powered recommendation engine to match everyone with the shoes that fit them best.

With top brand and retail partners across the world including New Balance, Bauer, The Athlete's Foot, Ecco and XXL, our footprint spans 2500+ stores across 46 countries, and counting.

Volumental’s data and machine learning platforms power all our products, communicate with 3000+ devices spread across six continents, and serve 18 million users - quickly growing. This brings in a large variation of data modalities including, 10s of millions of 3D scans, purchases, inventory, product catalog data, user interactions, and many more. To make this data useful and easy to work with, it is organized, indexed, and served in the different formats that satisfy the needs of our different products that build on top of it.

We are now looking for a data engineer to help us expand our analytics products - ensuring they have access to all the multi-modal data they require to provide an engaging, reliable, and fast experience.

8.gif [https://media.cdn.teamtailor.com/images/s3/teamtailor-production/gallery_picture/image_uploads/649887df-bd40-40e1-93ba-0812c220480b/original.gif]

What will you work on:
As a data engineer at Volumental, you will be designing, building, and maintaining scalable data pipelines and services on the Google Cloud Platform, working closely with a talented group of engineers and data scientists in our insights team. You will continuously improve data quality and performance of the data pipelines and collaborate with cross-functional teams, identifying opportunities for new features and improvements. For example, this may mean discovering a new product feature, realizing that it is not feasible given current data services, and then redesign or optimize how the relevant data is served to enable the new feature, working with the team to deliver it end-to-end.

We are excited about you because You:
Are a collaborative and kind team member.
Prefer simplicity over complexity and aim to discover clean solutions to complex problems.
Care about software design and can argue for and against different software design principles.
Share what you know with others and are humble to learn new things.
Care about the impact of your work end to end, feeling ownership rather than just solving tasks.
We expect you to:
Have at least three years of relevant experience as a software engineer or data engineer.
Have professional experience working in python and SQL. Experience in other languages is also valuable (E.g., Golang is common in our backend).
Have professional experience in different sql/nosql databases and can reason about when different kinds of databases are suitable.
Bonus - Don’t let the below stop you from applying, but if they fit you, please let us know!

You have experience in GCP.
Are interested in authentication and data security.
Have experience in providing data services for interactive dashboards.
Have worked with deployments or data volumes large enough that they could not be hosted on a single node.
Have used k8s, Terraform, or other comparable tools.
You'll be an essential part of the greater whole — able to drive initiatives and steer development while at the same time collaborating with other subject matter experts on our team. We encourage a diversity of candidates to apply!

Title: Azure Lead Developer
Description:
We are seeking an experienced Azure Lead Developer for our finance client in Stockholm.
Key experience and qualifications required
7+ years in IT and at least 4+ years of experience working on Azure Cloud
Hands on experience in Microsoft Azure covering - designing, implementing, testing, and maintaining cloud applications and related services
Strong understanding of core concepts - data storage, compute, data cleansing (ELT/ETL) and data engineering concepts
Clear understanding of core cloud concepts – IaaS, PaaS, SaaS, know-how of security – both data and platform
Hands on experience working with Azure Data bricks
Good Experience working with Azure DevOps, Generic CI/CD process and Dev ops tools such as GIT/Jenkins/Maven
Strong programming skill sets which may include – Python, Scala, Java (At least one)
Knowledge and exposure to structured and semi structured data, related file formats, partitioning strategies, effective and efficient storage of data in relational and non-relational storages
Valuable experience and qualifications
Azure Certifications – Azure Fundamentals, Azure Developer, Azure Data Engineer
Experience working with Azure Data Factory, Azure Cosmos, Azure Functions, Azure Machine Learning
Experience with relational SQL and NoSQL databases
Detail-oriented analytical and problem-solving skills
End to end data pipeline development and unit testing experience
Language
Fluent English. Swedish is valuable but not compulsory.
Working arrangements

Start ASAP, initially for 3 months.
You must have an existing right to work in Sweden without sponsorship in order to apply.

Title: BI-kompetens till Sogeti Luleå
Description:
Ansök nu
Data & AI är ett fokuserat satsningsområde som genomsyrar Sogeti lokalt, nationellt och globalt. Följ med oss på en spännande resa!
Vi söker dig som vill jobba med ny teknik inom området för BI, data management med roller som BI-utvecklare, Data Engineer, Data Scientist och Data Analyst!
Data & AI handlar för oss främst om att skapa möjligheter för våra kunder att fatta bättre affärsbeslut, att förstå kundernas verksamhet samt att kunna fokusera på kundnytta. Vi arbetar brett inom fältet och älskar nya tekniker; med allt från nyutveckling i framkant till förvaltning och med tekniker som till exempel Azure Data Faktory, Azure Data Lake, Databricks, Machine Learning och Power BI. Vårt främsta fokus är verktyg inom Microsoft BI-sviten men teknik är alltid underordnat kundnytta, vi gör det som är bäst för våra kunder!
Inom Sogeti finns det många hjälpsamma och glada kollegor med stor erfarenhet inom området. Vi prioriterar en balans mellan arbete och fritid högt och har en familjär arbetskultur. Det finns även ett brett nätverk inom hela Sogeti som hjälper dig att bredda och spetsa dina kunskaper.
Som BI-utvecklare på Sogeti Luleå kommer du att hjälpa våra kunder både genom strategiska och operativa förbättringar, få spännande inblick i en rad olika verksamheter och utveckla din egen kompetens!
Vem söker vi?
Du trivs i rollen som konsult i framkant, med möjlighet att växa och få ett omväxlande arbete. Vi tror att du är fokuserad, lösningsorienterad, nyfiken, analytisk och tekniskt skicklig. Du kan arbeta självgående och du brinner för ditt område och vill ha möjligheter att vidareutvecklas.

Vi tror att du kanske har erfarenhet av eller vill jobba med nya tekniker inom:
Azure, Cloud
Modern data plattform
Data/ data management
Azure Data Faktory/Data Lake och Databricks
Vi tror att du har:
Minst 3 års dokumenterad erfarenhet inom BI
Relevant teknisk högskoleutbildning
Erfarenhet av Power BI
Kunskaper om datalager, SSIS, SSRS, SSAS
Erfarenhet av SQL Server
Du talar och skriver flytande svenska och uttrycker dig väl i tal och skrift på engelska.

Title: Senior BI Analyst (Stockholm, Sweden)
Description:
As Google Cloud's premier partner in AI, we provide world-class businesses with cutting-edge data solutions in the cloud. We help clients take leading technology to the limits by combining our expertise in machine learning, data engineering, and analytics. With Google Cloud as our foundation, we help businesses future-proof their solutions, deepen their understanding of consumers, increase competitive advantage and unlock operational efficiencies.

Our team consists of experts in machine learning, data science, software engineering, mathematics, and design. We share a passion for data & analysis, operate at the cutting edge, and believe in a pragmatic approach to solving hard problems.
THE ROLE
You will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining analytics solutions, with a primary focus on business unit-specific data marts, self-service data models, building front-end analytical visualisations/reports (typically Looker), and training business users.
You will help deploy analytical data models, advise clients on development, and conduct co-development sessions to share your knowledge with customers. Being able to understand what technologies make a BI function a success; you will also have a good understanding of data warehouse technology on offer such as BigQuery and Snowflake.
This job is perfect for an individual who loves sharing their technical knowledge with others in a hands-on manner, thrives on working with different clients in just about every industry and proactively contributes to the open-source community.
As a Senior BI Analyst you will work alongside:
Analytics engineers: Responsible for designing, building, and maintaining end-to-end business intelligence solutions, with a primary focus on enterprise-wide data warehouse design, data models, and storage optimisation. Typically with DBT, snowflake/Bigquery and Google Cloud.
Architects: Responsible for designing the solution and data architectures. data architects design the end-to-end business intelligence solutions with a focus on designing the most optimal data model and architecture solution.
Data Engineers: Responsible for building applications which connect systems, collect data, process that data into a useful format. Often this data is ‘big’ and requires distributed frameworks to move and process. A data engineer is a key cog in a data platform as they look after the acquisition of data for analytics, and connecting the output of analytics to operational systems.
Your responsibilities will include:
Platform implementations:
Design and Build self service business intelligence platforms (usually Looker)
Build unit-specific data marts using dbt
Gain a deep understanding of the Looker Platform and Google Bigquery
Gain a understanding of the wider modern data stack
Work with analytics Engineers who design big data warehouses and advise on infrastructure decisions
Insights for Clients:
Produce actionable and insightful visualisations and dashboards from large, complex datasets in many different fields
Gather requirements of businesses challenges and enable them to make better decisions by analysing data and storytelling
Collaboration:
Share your knowledge of these tools through co-development and training sessions for clients
Work in a collaborative way with our customers and other team members
Actively propose solutions to fulfil our customer’s goals and requirements
Work closely with our tech partners: Google Cloud, Looker, Snowflake,dbt, fivetran.
Requirements
Essential:
Experience with Looker and/or Tableau or similar leading BI tools
Experience in the Google Cloud, AWS or Azure environment
Proficiency in SQL & GIT
Experience translating business requirements into technical solutions
Ability to communicate complex ideas in a simple way to a wide range of audiences
Proven analytical and problem-solving skills
Experience in a client-facing position, ideally in a BI consultancy
Bonus Points:
Previous experience with Looker, dbt, Snowflake or BigQuery
Experience in CI/CD principles
Benefits
The Basics: 30 days holiday in addition to bank holidays, Private Occupational Pension (Salary Sacrifice), Team Bonus payable annually.
Health & Wellness: 4500 kr Private Health Insurance Allowance per year, 5000 kr Wellness Allowance per year, Employee Assistance Program

Learning: 8500 kr Conference Budget + 4 days attendance per year, Access to Linux Academy, Coursera, and LinkedIn Learning
Career Development: A personalised development plan to ensure you hit your professional goals with a clear roadmap for progression
Impact: The opportunity to work on cutting-edge AI and ML solutions spanning multiple industries and with market-leading organisations
Innovation: Access to Datatonic LABs, our Research & Development hub. Experiment and bring forward ideas, create impactful and meaningful work in a creative and collaborative environment - even just for fun!
Flexible Working: A mix of office and remote working, 1200 kr Home Equipment Allowance
Team Vibe & Social: A welcoming and friendly team plus weekly Team Lunches and Monthly Social Events

WORKING FOR DATATONIC
We’re an eclectic team with lots of different interests and personalities. We have many different roles across data science, engineering, analytics, consulting, marketing, business development, and operations. We have offices in the UK, Stockholm, Geneva, Munich, and Barcelona, and we work with clients in many other European countries. We allow for flexible working hours and the possibility of remote work.
As a company, we have a strong emphasis on learning and professional development. Our core values are:

Cultivating Excellence
A hub for continuous learning, curiosity, developing ideas, testing things out - and then putting ‘excellence’ into practice.
Owning It
Working collaboratively in cross-functional teams to achieve customer delight. We love what we do and draw immense satisfaction from taking responsibility and seeing the results of our work.
Purposeful Impact
Creating positive change for our customers, using the most relevant machine learning and analytics approaches and the best technologies to meet real business needs.
Winning with Partners & Friends
Our business has been built on great partnerships and open-source collaboration. It’s one thing to be successful, but to do it in partnership with great people and other great companies is even better in our opinion.
Datatonic is committed to being an equal opportunities employer. Diversity, equity and inclusion are a key part of our values and central to our overall mission of recruiting, retaining and promoting a diverse mix of colleagues. We encourage applications from all backgrounds, abilities and communities. If you require any accommodations or adjustments to our interview process, please reach out to jobs@datatonic.com and we will do our best to assist you.

Title: Software Developer C++ till SSAB i Oxelösund
Description:
Software Developer C++ till SSAB i Oxelösund
Sök jobbet
Sista ansökningsdag 2023-02-10
Nu söker vi en Software Developer med kunskaper inom C++ till SSABs egenutvecklade processtyrningssystem i Oxelösund
Har du kunskaper inom C/C++ och Python? Bra! Då kan du vara den Software Developer / mjukvaruutvecklare som bidrar till att möjliggöra SSABs digitala transformation mot industri 4.0! För rollen som utvecklare letar vi efter dig som är nyfiken och motiveras av att få arbeta i SSABs egenutvecklade automationsverktyg, i syfte att förbättra och förenkla i produktionen.

Låter det som något för dig? Välkommen med din ansökan!

Ditt anställningserbjudande
Som utvecklare förväntas du utveckla och förvalta befintlig mjukvara i det egenutvecklade programmet ProviewR. Du förväntas bidra med att förbättra programspråket och arbeta med kontinuerliga förbättringar av mjukvaran.
Rollen innebär att du har ett stor eget ansvar och en frihet att lägga upp ditt arbete. Du ingår i IT avdelningen och kommer till ett utvecklingsteam beståendes av 11 kollegor med omfattande kompetens och som har ett tätt samarbete.


Gym på kontoret

Jobba hemma

Tjänstepension

Friskvård
Dina arbetsuppgifter
I rollen som Software Developer är dina arbetsuppgifter att:
Utveckla och underhålla SSABs automationsverktyg ProviewR
Följa utvecklingen inom automationsområdet och närliggande områden
Ge support till användare av ProviewR
Hålla utbildningar i ProviewR
Upprätta dokumentation och handledningar för ProviewR
Värt att veta
Totalt på SSAB i Oxelösund arbetar ca 2400 personer och produktionen pågår dygnet runt. Tjänsten är placerad i Oxelösund och du förväntas arbeta på plats 1-2 dagar i veckan, utöver dessa dagar finns möjlighet att arbeta hemma. Du kommer till ett hängivet team med en engagerad ledare som ger stor frihet under ansvar.
Våra förväntningar
Vi söker dig som är utbildad ingenjör inom data, gärna inom realtidssystem. Kanske arbetar du idag som Dataingenjör, Data Engineer, Embedded-utvecklare?
För rollen behöver du ha kunskaper inom:
C/C++
Linux
Phyton
Har du dessutom kunskaper inom:
Proview
JavaScript/TypeScript
SQL - GTK+ och QT ramverken
Containers ex. Docker och Kubernetes
Embedded-utveckling på ARM
Ethernet-stacken, Modbus, Profibus och Profinet
I rollen förväntas du bidra till problemlösning och därför söker vi dig med en god logisk förmåga och ett lösningsorienterat arbetssätt. Vi tror att du som person är nyfiken, driven och får saker att hända. Du har ett strukturerat arbetssätt och har en kommunikativ förmåga då du har en nära dialog och samverkan internt.
Lär känna SSAB – din framtida arbetsgivare
SSAB är ett Norden- och USA-baserat stålföretag. SSAB erbjuder mervärdesprodukter och tjänster som har utvecklats i nära samarbete med företagets kunder för att skapa en starkare, lättare och mer hållbar värld. SSAB har 14000 anställda i över 50 länder. Idag har SSAB produktionsanläggningar i Sverige, Finland och USA. SSAB är börsnoterat på NASDAQ OMX Nordic Exchange i Stockholm och sekundärnoterat på NASDAQ OMX i Helsingfors. www.ssab.com
Avstånd till arbetsplatsen
Aspaleden 2. Öppna Google Maps för att räkna ut resvägen till din framtida arbetsplats.
Söktips från Jenny Nilsson – din rekryterare!
Jag tycker att du ska söka jobbet eftersom:
SSAB är världsledande när det gäller höghållfasta stål och den största stålproducenten i Norden!
Rollen innebär stor påverkningsgrad och möjlighet för dig att utveckla mjukvaran och se den driftsättas!
Du får möjligheten att vara en del i SSAB:s vision att skapa en fossilfri värdekedja, från gruvan till slutprodukt!

Frågor om jobbet? Hör av dig till mig
Jenny Nilsson

Sista ansökningsdag 2023-02-10

Du får möjligheten att vara en del i SSAB:s vision att skapa en fossilfri värdekedja, från gruvan till slutprodukt!

Frågor om jobbet? Hör av dig till mig
Jenny Nilsson

Title: BI Backend Developer till Martin & Servera-gruppen
Description:
Martin & Servera är inne i en spännande digitaliseringsresa. Vår digitala transformation har stor strategisk bäring och vi satsar mycket på att kunna erbjuda våra kunder en kundupplevelse i absoluta världsklass. Ett essentiellt delmål i den här resan är att bemästra all intressant data som flödar genom våra system, och vi är därför på jakt efter en BI Backend Developer till vårt team Data & Analytics. Genom att säkerställa att data flödar genom vår dataplattform utgör du en viktig roll i förverkligandet av målet om Martin & Servera som datadrivet bolag.

BI Backend Developer
Som leverantör av allt en restaurang kan behöva - från servis till råvaror och systemstöd, är vi branschledande, och en livsviktig kraft i den svenska restaurangbranschen. I rollen som BI Backend Developer kommer du modernisera den här kraften genom att bygga smarta och effektiva datalösningar i vår miljö som snurrar i Azure. Du bidrar således till ett mer datadrivet dagligt arbete så väl som på strategisk nivå genom hela koncernen.
Martin & Servera är en arbetsplats som prioriterar trivsel och work-life balance. Hos oss är det viktigt att du som medarbetare mår bra, och för många kan det faktum att man kan påverka sin egen arbetsdag till viss del hjälpa till. Hämtning och lämning på förskola, hantverkare hemma etc.... allt det där som också måste fungera i livet för att man ska må bra på jobbet!

Roll och Ansvar
Du kommer vara en del av vårt team Data & Analytics som är en central del i den strategiska satsningen på Martin & Serveras digitaliseringsresa. Rollen kommer i huvudsak fokusera på nyutveckling, och i förlängningen ett möjliggörande av datadrivet beslutsfattande inom Martin & Servera-gruppen i sin helhet. Viktiga delar av ditt ansvar är att utveckla datamodellen, sätta upp ETL-flöden, designa nya lösningar, samt hjälpa verksamheten med förslag på nya lösningar kring hur data kan förenkla och förbättra beslutsfattande.
Du har troligtvis arbetat ett par år i en liknande roll där du har skaffat dig erfarenhet av Microsofts BI-stack och dimensionsmodellering. Som person är du självgående, och du trivs i en miljö där du ges stor frihet i ditt arbete. Du kommer slutligen gärna med förslag på bättre lösningar samt är orädd inför att utmana status quo när det behövs.

För att lyckas i rollen tror vi att du:
Har 2-3 års erfarenhet som BI-Utvecklare i backend, Data Engineer, eller motsvarande.
Har erfarenhet i Microsofts BI-stack.
Har erfarenhet inom dimensionsmodellering.
Är initiativtagande, självgående och kreativ.
Är flytande i svenska, i tal och skrift.
Det är meriterande om du:
Har erfarenhet i Azure.
Har erfarenhet inom objektorienterad programmering.
Har erfarenhet inom agil utveckling.

Varmt välkommen med din ansökan! Urval och intervjuer sker löpande. Skicka därför in din ansökan redan idag!

Anställningsform: Tillsvidare, heltid
Tillträde: Enligt överenskommelse
Bolag: Martin & Servera AB. Grosshandlarvägen 7, Årsta
Kontakt: För frågor om tjänsten kontakta Björn Larsson Gerdén på bjorn.gerden@martinservera.se, för frågor om urvalsprocessen kontakta Andreas Rasmuson på andreas.rasmuson@martinservera.se
Facklig företrädare: Anna-Lena Holsteryd, al.holsteryd@martinservera.se
Urvalsprocessen
För att ta reda på om just du är den vi söker använder vi oss av personlighetstest och intervjuer i alla våra rekryteringar. Det gör vi för att kunna jämföra kandidater som uppfyller grundkraven på ett så rättvist sätt som möjligt. Du kan läsa mer om testerna och vår urvalsprocess här. Observera att vi även gör bakgrundskontroll vid samtliga rekryteringar.

Martin & Servera-gruppen
Martin & Servera-gruppen är en svensk koncern till 100 % ägda av Axel Johnson-gruppen. Vi är Sveriges ledande restaurang- och storköksspecialist. Vi består av sjutton bolag med starka varumärken specialiserade inom olika delar i grossistledet. Vi erbjuder råvaror, utrustning, drycker, tjänster och utbildningar till våra kunder, som är allt från stora restaurang- och hotellkedjor till det minsta lokala bageriet. Vi drivs av starka värderingar och en vision om hållbara affärer med omtanke om människor, djur och miljö. Läs mer om Martin & Servera-gruppen här.

Title: DevOps Engineer
Description:
Humly is a digital marketplace revolutionising how teachers and nurses work within schools and nurseries. We're the market leader in Sweden and have scaled up to become the same for the UK market, where we have a first-mover advantage.
To support this growth we are creating a brand new development team in our Gothenburg HQ. The team will focus on backend, API, data and DevOps, and supercharge our app developers to deliver value. Together with a Data Engineer and a Senior Backend developer, you will help create a system that’s: performant, secure, observable, measurable, automated and that allows incremental daily deployments with feature flagging.
As an early member, you'll be essential in establishing a high-performing team and will have a big influence on the work process, tooling, and tech stack, plus hiring and growing the team.
About the Role
You will take responsibility for our infrastructure and CI/CD pipelines. We do weekly deployments, but want to get even faster and allow our developers to push daily to production. You will work to eliminate bottlenecks, ensure low boundaries between Dev and Ops, and support the organisation to operate as we scale.
You probably have
Great sense of good-enough solutions but always thinking about trade-offs
Experience with automation and CI/CD pipelines
Worked with setting up observability and error tracking for production environments
Experience with configuration as code (terraform)
Experience with AWS, and in particular ECS
Ideas how to enable devs to push to prod fast, and revert if they screw up
It would be even better if you have
Previously set up mechanisms for evaluating success of deployments
Worked with feature flag deploys
Experience organising an on-call workflow for high availability
And amazing if you have experience with these technologies
Ruby on Rails (our legacy API backend)
MongoDB (our legacy database)
GraphQL and REST (our API interface)
Python (some of our analytics and integrations)
React for web and native (our apps)
Typescript
PostgreSQL or EdgeDB
What we offer
Lots of influence as an early member in small team
Be part of an entrepreneurial and playful journey. We grow by researching, testing and learning Your ideas matter
Interesting work with data as a product
Opportunity to define your role within the company
Hybrid office model - flexibility with responsibility. Sometimes it's great to sit together; sometimes you want to focus at home
Salary range starting at 43 000 SEK/month
Collective agreement with pension scheme
International environment with locations in Sweden and UK (English is the company language)
A Viking Venture community of 20+ other companies to learn and share knowledge with
Contribute to a globally important and exciting solution that creates immense value for our users and all the children and students they meet every day
How we hire
We recruit continuously, so don’t wait – send us your application now!

Initial screening - An initial, casual 30-minute conversation with our CTO about Humly’s short and long-term goals. And how they relate to yours.This is a good time to chat through any concerns or deal breakers you may have.
Assignment or reference case - We don’t want the technical interview phase to start from scratch, and we don’t believe in white board coding. This step ensures a more collaborative and engaging discussion in the next phase.
The tech chat- A one-hour deep-dive into the craft of software development with a couple of our team members. With the assignment or reference case as a backdrop, we let you describe how you engage with problem-solving. You'll share your opinions about technical debt, project management, and your favourite tech stacks. This is a golden opportunity for you to learn more about Humly, and why our team enjoys working here. So ask us questions. And please, don't be afraid to ask the hard ones – be very afraid. Kidding.
The experience chat - A 1-hour talk with our CTO and one of our founders about your previous experiences and learnings. Share your successes – and failures – and all the permutations in between. Our goal is to understand how what you’ve done before has shaped your perspective about the who/what/when/where/ and why of what you want to do next.
About Humly
Humly is a digital marketplace connecting supply teachers and schools. 70 million teachers are needed globally to reach the 2030 UN sustainable development goals, and our mission is to solve a big piece of that puzzle.
Humly has financially strong and active owners in Viking Ventures, and have raised €10M. We're in a scale-up phase in the UK with high ambitions. The UK market alone is worth $2 billion, and Humly has a first mover advantage.
We have 60 employees working at our offices in Gothenburg, Sweden and Fareham, Milton Keynes, Manchester and Birmingham in the UK. And over 3,000 registered teachers plus agreements with over 4,000 schools in Sweden and the UK.
The Humly platform consists of multiple web clients written in React.js and mobile apps for iOS and Android written in React Native. All connect via GraphQL and REST to a Ruby on Rails API. Data is stored in a MongoDB database and temporarily cached in Redis. The infrastructure is run on Amazon Web Services with Infrastructure As Code approach.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer som vill skapa framtida historia
Description:
Hej!

Hur vill du att framtiden ser ut?


Vi på Artificial Collective
vill skapa framtida historia med AI! Tillsammans med de mest passionerade inom AI/Data, inspirerar vi varandra varje dag och riktar vår samlade kunskap mot att skapa de bästa AI-lösningarna som bidrar med en större nytta. Både för samhället och enskilda företag.
Idag samarbetar vi med några av de mest spännande företagen i Norden!

Bli en del av teamet ‍‍
som idag består av seniora konsulter inom Data Science och Machine Learning. För att fortsätta arbeta med de mest spännande projekten, söker vi just nu efter vår nästa kollega inom Machine Learning.
Som anställd eller egen konsult hos Artificial Collective får du möjligheten att arbeta med just det ditt hjärta bultar extra för, oavsett om det gäller nyutveckling, vidareutveckling eller förvaltning. Både i individuella och i teamprojekt.
Du själv bestämmer över din tid, ersättning, vad du vill arbeta med och i vilken riktning du vill utvecklas. Som en del av Artificial Collective, får du en dedikerad agent som tillsammans med dig ser till att du kommer dit! Exempelvis genom utbildning, inspiration eller med hjälp av mentorskap från en expert inom önskat område.

Vi tror att du brinner för
Designa, bygga, driftsätta Machine Learning lösningar.

Ta komplex data till modeller och analyser som ger nya insikter.
Ta fram, träna och utvärdera ML-modeller för stora mängder användardata för att driva beslut.
Programmera i lämpligt språk så som Python, Scala och SQL.

Vårt löfte
är att ge dig vad du behöver för att du ska kunna lägga mer tid på det som ditt hjärta bultar extra för!
Vi tror på frihet och att det skapar välmående vilket vi ser som avgörande för passion samt geniala idéer.
Vi tror på passion och att det är viktigt för glädje och fortsatt lärande. Vi vill frigöra din passion.
‍‍ Vi tror på styrkan i att arbeta tillsammans och rikta vår kollektiva passion mot visionära idéer och skapa bättre lösningar.
Samtidigt får du det bästa paketet av förmåner.
Lön: 40-80k/månad
Semester: 30-60 betalda dagar
Pension: Ja
Försäkringar: Ja
Friskvård: Ja

Visst låter det intressant?
Sök direkt och var med och skapa den framtida historian du vill se när vi tillsammans tar nästa stora steg inom AI!

Title: Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD
Description:
Join us on our journey to net zero and make an impact on the mobility of tomorrow. We are looking for a Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD to join our R&D team.
Aurobay has over hundred years of heritage in creating premium quality engines. With homes in Sweden and China, we have a strong reputation for pioneering practices in the automotive industry. We pride ourselves in our attention to detail and commitment to excellence.

Your role at Aurobay
Our team currently consists of six data scientists, SW engineers, and model-based calibration engineers. We develop new methods for measurement data collection and analysis to help R&D become more efficient and data driven. We also work closely with other advanced engineering teams.
As Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD, you will:
Train and evaluate ML models for predicting emissions
Work closely together with subject matter experts to align data/measurement requirements and incorporate physical models into the model
Optimize algorithm memory and CPU load for predictions on the edge together with function developers
You will also use the data we are collecting in our rigs to build models for predicting engine emissions of hazardous species. The models can be used both offline in the development phase, and on the edge for On-Board Monitoring (OBM) and On-Board Diagnostics (OBD) in our customer vehicles. As part of this job, you’ll have the opportunity develop your own machine-learning projects together with the rest of the team. We give our engineers the freedom and time for their own projects, to try out new ideas and fine-tune their skills.
What we offer
In addition to a competitive salary, a great location on Lindholmen, and a genuine work-life balance, we provide the following benefits:
A yearly wellness contribution of SEK 5 000 for your physical and mental wellbeing.
A personal and professional development scheme to support your growth.
Want to drive a car? – Discount to buy a car, and a competitive leasing cost for a company car.
Additional pension funding.
Competitive additional and full coverage insurance.


Do you fit the profile?
You hold a master’s degree or higher in data science, mathematics, statistics, physics or relevant fields.
You have strong programming skills in Python, Julia, or MATLAB.
You also have experience in ML algorithms such as linear regression, artificial neural networks, and boosted decision tree regression.
Good to have familiarity with:
Time series modeling, especially ML algorithms that can be used for time series such as recurrent neural networks, convolutional neural networks, or transformers
Internal Combustion Engines
Chemical models for catalytic converters
Embedded systems
At Aurobay, we are committed to diversity and inclusion. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and believe that different perspectives and experiences make for a stronger, more innovative company.
How to apply
To apply, please submit your application via the link below. Deadline to submit your application is 31st of January, but the selection process will be running continuously. Please note that due to GDPR, we do not accept applications via email.
We can’t wait to see what you can bring to our team!
Questions
If you have any additional questions regarding the position, you are welcome to contact recruiting manager Erik Fyrk, erik.fyrk@aurobay.com. For questions regarding the recruitment process please contact Recruiter Felicia Eriksson, felicia.eriksson@aurobay.com.
Unionen: Ordf Joakim Dahlin, joakim.dahlin@volvocars.com, tel +46734630172
Ledarna: Ordf Håkan Modigh, hakan.modigh@volvocars.com, tel +46733333801
Akademikerna: Ordf. Henrik Simonsen, henrik.simonsen@aurobay

Title: Machine Learning Engineer to Prisjakt
Description:
Prisjakt has historical data about millions of products, prices from tens of thousands of stores, and user behaviour data from millions of users. With this data we help users in seven countries to make better decisions every day, but we would like to help them even more.
You will be a part of the Data/ML team at Prisjakt which is responsible for a large variety of tasks. We do analyses and reports for everyone at Prisjakt, create foundations for insights that are communicated to the media, automate indexing of data from stores, and develop algorithms for recommendations and personalization. Regardless of what task you’re working on, you will always have the support of a helpful and competent team.
Things on your todo
In collaboration with data scientists, apply software engineering design and best practises to operationalize ML prototypes into scalable solutions
Working with large data sets and real time streaming services.
Bringing code to production
Train, evaluate and serve ML models
Being in charge of the entire lifecycle (design, experimentation, development. deployment, monitoring, and maintenance)
We think you’re one of those peeps that loves turning raw data into valuable insights and actions. You are curious and like to keep up with new trends. You make things happen and happily share your knowledge with your coworkers.
Must have
A strong background in machine learning
Experience of Tensorflow and/or Scikit-learn
Awesome programming skills in Python and SQL
Good communication skills in English
Bonus points if you have
Cloud experience like Google Cloud, AWS or Azure
Worked with Kubernetes
Experience with Kafka and streaming data
Digital image analysis
Where: Even though we are a hybrid company, we’d love it if you wanted to spend time with the team in the studios in Malmö or Ängelholm.
When: We would like you to start tomorrow but we understand that you have obligations today and those need to be handed over first.
We want you to feel: Finally Monday!
At Prisjakt, you don’t need a work persona. Our dearest principle is that you’re welcome just as you are. We’ve made it our mission to make you feel excited about Mondays and also make it easier for you to manage the hassle of everyday life. We are proud of our relaxed and familiar atmosphere. In addition to working, you will also be able to fix your torn jeans in our creative workshop or learn how to make a proper espresso. With our epic printer Printz Charming, we dress our walls with whatever art we like, and our scooter swiftly gets you to your lunch date. Kids are always welcome, and you are free to borrow tools from the workshop for your home improvement projects.
If you’re curious to know more about life at Prisjakt, our benefits or why we exist you should definitely explore our career site.
Want to meet our brilliant people and get a feel for the vibe at our studios? Make sure to follow us on Instagram @Prisjaktlife.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
MACHINE LEARNING ENGINEER

As a member of the ML-team you will be working with a broad range of problems with one common denominator – ML will be the key ingredient.

You will have to analyze the problem at hand, come up with a solution strategy and execute it. This typically entails gaining an in-depth understanding of the challenge, understanding the available data, and then re-formulating it as an ML problem. It requires openness, creativity, and an eagerness to learn new methodology and explore new terrains.
We approach these problems as a team, meaning that you will have to be able to clearly explain your reasoning and code in order to engage the rest of us.
NOTE:
Right now we are looking for ML Engineers with +2 years of experience with ML in production. To apply you need to have a work permit for Sweden.

Our Stack

Python / R – standard open-source libraries
Scikit-learn and various specialized Python and R ML libraries
Deep learning frameworks such as Pytorch and Tensorflow/Keras
Cloud platforms such as GCP, AWS, and Azure
Relational database management systems
Distributed processing such as Apache Spark

Responsibilities

Analyzing and planning problems, solutions, and delivery
Preprocessing, feature engineering, and dataset creation
ML model development
Validation of results
Data pipelining and infrastructure development

Background & Skills

MSc or Ph.D. in a quantitative field
Excellent understanding of a broad set of ML algorithms and frameworks
A passion for lean, clean, and maintainable code
The desire to grow and to share insights with others
Experience from ML i production

Helpful knowledge

Deep learning frameworks and theory
Data pipelining and infrastructure
DevOps experience, CI/CD, Kubernetes

About Team Modulai

At Modulai we focus 100% on solving problems with machine learning (ML). We work in teams on a project basis. We work for clients, as part of the core team in startups where we have long-time engagement as well as building our own ML products.
Learning and teamwork are central to how we work. Everyone in the team is or will soon be a full-stack ML engineer capable of scoping and developing end-to-end ML solutions. You should be able to do end-to-end machine learning products by yourself but actually, never do it because we always work in teams. If there is data, we will do ML on it!
