Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
Machine Learning Engineer
Our Business Intelligence & Analytics team is providing consulting services to clients in the Nordic region from our office in Stockholm based on the latest technology leading platform providers such as Microsoft, Amazon and Google. The demand around cloud based analytical platforms is constantly growing and we are now looking for candidates with strong technical competence and a can-do attitude. You will take part in our client implementation projects to help and guide our clients to become more data-driven and AI-driven.
The team you will be joining is responsible for delivering an end-to-end Machine Learning solution, from building MLOps platform, model training to machine learning powered software development.
As a Machine Learning Engineer, you will apply your knowledge of data science, machine learning and software engineering to implement and run machine learning workloads on Cloud; in particular, using Databricks and Azure Machine Learning Service. This entails planning and creating a suitable working environment for machine learning workloads on Azure, running experiments and training models, managing, deploying and monitoring machine learning models in production.
Requirements
University Degree from Computer Science, Software Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent
Preferably 1-3 years of experience as Machine Learning Engineer, Data Scientist, Software Engineer, or DevOps Engineer
Knowledge of machine learning algorithms and practical experience of machine learning model development
Strong software development skills and proficiency in one or more programming languages, e.g., Python, Scala, C++
Experience in developing CI/CD pipelines for DataOps, DevOps and MLOps purposes
Preferably, you have
Experience of using machine learning platforms like MLflow
Experience of development with Git and Shell under Linux
Familiar with Databricks, Azure Machine Learning and Data Lake
Experience in technical consulting projects
Fluent in English and good communication skills
Swedish on conversation level is beneficial
You are
Social team-player with drive and positive attitude
Analytical and driven
A person with “Can-do mentality”
You would like to work with us if you
Want to work with the latest technology and projects within in Analytics and AI
Are motivated by customer challenges
Like to work in teams and are humble
We offer, part from a competitive salary, also
Pension
Healthcare allowance
Skills development
Monthly social activities
Joint out of work activities and annual adventures

Title: Machine Learning Engineer till Griffeye
Description:
Fluent Swedish is a requirement, therefore the application is in Swedish.

Machine Learning Engineer till Griffeye
Vi växer och söker nya kollegor till vårt Machine Learning team på Griffeye. Här jobbar du med hela Machine Learning-stacken, från problemanalys och träning, till deployment och integration. Produkterna används av polismyndigheter världen över för att analysera enorma mängder bild och video. Med AI och Computer Vision kommer du hjälpa till att göra den här analysen effektivare och göra verklig skillnad för våra användare och samhället i stort.

Omfattning: Heltid, 100%.
Start: Omgående (med hänsyn till ev. uppsägningstid)
Ort: Göteborg
Vilka är vi?
Griffeye utvecklar och tillhandahåller mjukvara och mjukvarulösningar som hjälper polisen i omfattande utredningar av stora mängder digital media (bild och video) i synnerhet i fall av sexuella övergrepp på barn. Griffeye är världsledande inom sitt område och teknikplattformen Griffeye Analyze används idag av över 4 000 polismyndigheter världen över. Plattformens innovativa tekniska lösningar, däribland artificiell intelligens, ansiktsigenkänning, och en öppen arkitektur för storskaligt polissamarbete, resulterar i att polismyndigheter världen över kan lösa de mest komplexa fall snabbare och mer effektivt.
Vi arbetar i tvärfunktionella team bestående av utvecklare, testare och designers. Hos oss finns det en stark gemenskap och de flesta av oss har arbetat många år inom Safer Society Group. Genom nära samarbete, korta beslutsvägar och en gemensam känsla av att vi faktiskt bidrar till ett bättre samhälle har Griffeye kommit långt på bara några år.
Hur det är att jobba som utvecklare hos oss
Griffeye Brain, vårt AI-verktyg, är utvecklat med Python och Deep Learning-frameworks som TensorFlow/Keras, medans Griffeye Analyze-plattformen huvudsakligen utvecklas med C#, .NET och SQL. Som en full stack Machine Learning Engineer, kommer du arbeta både med träning av nya modeller för att utöka Griffeye Brains funktioner, och med att ta de nya funktionerna till våra kunder, integrerade i Griffeye Analyze-plattformen.

Mycket av det vi gör är nyutveckling eftersom vi alltid vill förbättra vår produkt och ge våra kunder ett effektivare verktyg. Det är dock lika viktigt för oss att vi aktivt hjälper till med supporten av våra kunder samt hanterar vår tekniska skuld löpande. Eftersom vi alltid vill vara först med den senaste tekniken inom vårt område utvecklar vi i ett högt tempo, men bortprioriterar aldrig kvalitén.

Nya idéer tar vi fram genom att löpande bolla förslag med varandra och diskutera olika lösningar. Dessutom tycker vi det är viktigt att ta tid till att testa nya saker för att fortsätta utvecklas. Därför har vi exempelvis regelbundna projektdagar där alla har möjlighet att fokusera på sina egna utvecklingsmål och jobba mer innovativt på egen hand. Det som driver oss i vårt arbete är vetskapen om att vår produkt gör stor skillnad i samhället. Men även om vi arbetar med allvarliga saker är det för oss minst lika viktigt att ha roligt på jobbet. Våra dagar innefattar en stor dos humor (ofta rätt kass), många skratt och diverse aktiviteter vid sidan av arbetet. Tillsammans äter vi hamburgare på torsdagar, springer på luncherna, spelar padel och utmanar varandra i brädspel. Har du någon favoritburgare? Annars har vi några riktigt bra förslag.
Självklart exponeras du aldrig för känsligt/olagligt bild- och videomaterial i ditt arbete på Griffeye.

Title: Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
We’re Findify by Maropost, an agile team focused on delivering the industry’s best search and merchandising tool for ecommerce. A fully remote team with great experience & grand ambitions, spread around all over Europe.

Headquartered in Downtown Toronto with offices also in Australia, India, and Europe, Maropost is the leader in unified commerce for the midmarket! Our Software as a Service platform provides organizations with the ability to connect with their customers across Ecommerce, Retail, Marketing, Service and Search Clouds to unify the customer experience as well as to provide efficiency, value, and ROI to their organizations.

About the Position:
As a Machine Learning Engineer, you'll be one of the owners of our personalisation and recommendations engine. It consists of many moving parts, starting with data collection, processing it via Flink and all the way to ML model development, training, serving and A/B testing.
As an expert in your field, you will be empowered to steer the future direction of our ML capabilities and will be, together with the help of the core backend team, responsible for serving the innovations to our customers in an efficient and reliable way.
We’re an empowered product team, firmly committed to collaborative problem solving. We write specs and share the decision making. We work in two-week sprints to deliver greatness.

The Opportunity:
We are looking for an open minded and enthusiastic data scientist for our Senior Machine Learning Engineer position to join our Machine Learning team. If you are interested in personalization and information retrieval and have experience in this field, we would love to meet you! We are a product driven team, so we’re looking for someone who loves to be engaged in the product development process and appreciates being able to deliver a feature without depending on other engineers.

About the Position:
As a data scientist on our Machine Learning team, you'll be one of the owners of our personalisation and recommendations engine. It consists of many moving parts, starting with data collection, processing it via Flink and all the way to ML model development, training, serving and A/B testing.
As an expert in your field, you will be empowered to steer the future direction of our ML capabilities and will be, together with the help of the core backend team, responsible for serving the innovations to our customers in an efficient and reliable way.
We’re an empowered product team, firmly committed to collaborative problem solving. We write specs and share the decision making. We work in two-week sprints to deliver greatness.

What You'll be Responsible for:
Designing and implementing maintainable ML services, and driving projects from start to finish.
Exploring explainable ML and control over it, we believe ML model's performance is already good and this has a huge growth potential.
Keeping up-to-date with advancements in the field of AI/ML to make sure our algorithms reflect the current state of the art.
Reading a lot of code, writing code with a focus on maintainability.
Contributing to technical and product specs, and collaborating on architecture and design decisions together with the other stakeholders.
Embracing feedback on your specs and your code as an opportunity for continuous improvement and collaborative design, and carrying out spec and code review for your coworkers.
Caring for knowledge transfer and mentoring others on the team, whether they're overall more junior or just less experienced in your specific domain of expertise.
Being an effective technical and non-technical communicator (our company language is English).

What You'll need to bring to Maropost
Have previous experience developing and iterating on machine learning models (We use Python to train our Learn-to-Rank model).
Have previous experience with serving and maintaining the ML model (We use Scala for to serve our models).
Understand statistics and experimental design.
Are comfortable reading and writing SQL queries.
Have previous experience working with data processing pipelines (we use Flink, but experience with Spark or similar tools will be sufficient).
Appreciate good developer experience and make ours even better by introducing new tools and iterating on processes.
Are generous with your communication, whether it is about new ideas, praise, or very kindly phrased constructive feedback.
Like to learn new things, have an open mind and want to share your knowledge with your coworkers.

What’s in it for you?
You will not only have the freedom to make this role your own but be part of helping grow the Retail Global brand and expand it into all our markets globally as we currently operate in North America, Europe and ANZ (Australia/New Zealand). If you want to work with other brilliant people in an extraordinary work culture and are eager to learn (and have fun) along the way, then Maropost is the place for you!


You'll also have access to these perks:
Extended Healthcare
Stock Options
Dental Care
Vision Care
Impact and culture
We are going into a growth phase so this is the perfect opportunity for you if you're excited about joining a team where you can have a lot of impact and take a lot of ownership over your work. The TypeScript team especially is a great opportunity for you if you want to leave your mark and contribute to the culture, as the team's position is becoming strategically more prominent with more of the core functionality of the software getting moved to the domain of the TypeScript team.

Developer experience
We are a high-tech company, and especially in the recent years we've focused a lot on developer experience. We have a cutting-edge tech stack (TypeScript and Scala with Kubernetes deployments) with no legacy tools and a keen interest in keeping it that way - so if you're excited about learning new technologies in a laid back, collaborative environment where quality software and engineering experience are among the first priorities, we are a good fit for you.

Work life balance
We're a remote team and have found this a recipe for success for the whole company. This has made us successful especially during the global pandemic where we've been able to grow the company and keep all positions intact while supporting our staff with young children and other family members to care for. We care about quality of work, collaborative processes and tangible results - we want you to be available and responsive during usual working hours in case your coworkers need something from you, but we’re very flexible when the circumstances arise. We have kids at home from daycare making appearances on calls sometimes, and you can book a slot in your work calendar for the appointment with your doctor or your dentist without feeling guilty. It’s important that we’re communicative and as responsive as possible when that happens, but sometimes we need some flexibility on when we get the focused work done and we understand that completely.

Equal Employment Opportunist:
Maropost is deeply committed to promoting diversity, advancing equity and fostering a culture of inclusion. Therefore, we invite applications from marginalized and equity-seeking groups. Individuals seeking employment at Maropost are considered without regards to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identification, national origin, age, marital status, ancestry, physical or mental disability, or veteran status. Accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process. Please feel free to alert us of any accommodations via hr@maropost.com.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
Who is ArK?
There are many consumer facing fintech products, but finance as a whole is virtually untouched by technology. Investment decisions are still being made out of pdf’s and “shark tank”-like processes rather than utilising the forecasting methods found at companies like Spotify or Google. This makes capital allocation riddled with bias and very ripe for disruption.
At ArK we’re convinced that by putting data and tech at the heart of finance we can impact how money flows and, in turn, create a more democratised and unbiased economy.
Today we offer founders access to our machine learning platform AIM. Through connecting their raw data we can fully understand what they’ve built without any bias; connecting what has been achieved historically into a simulated 5-year future. This prediction is the foundation for the transformational loans that we are able to issue, and a tool that founders get to keep for business optimisation.
AiM is using big data and machine learning to analyse and predict companies’ current and future performance, to be used as a foundation for our frontier credit decision making. All in all, we thrive in the win-win data modelling where insights are valuable both for ArK as a lender, but also for our customer as a growth company. We build AiM to push beyond “credit scoring”, and to become the unrivalled place to plug in your company data, and get back valuable insights for optimising company growth — when our customers grow efficiently, everybody wins.
Being an ML leader at ArK
ArK has one of the most diverse sets of company data in the world, and it is growing at an incredible pace. The diversity and richness of data we want you to work with is essentially unheard of as we get raw data directly from our customers’ IT systems, and we want your help to make sense of it, both for us, and for our customers. The challenges here are unlike anywhere else as we’re striving to build generalizable modelling solutions that can be applied across an incredibly broad range of company data and business models.
Some of the problems that we help our customers solve are figuring out really detailed customer lifetime values (e.g. placing a value on our customers’ customers) and projecting their future revenue and cost growth — which conveniently enough is excellent data to base lending decisions on and tailor financing solutions to.
We’re also exploring advanced user churn modelling, credit scoring, customer business clustering and performance benchmarking and various clustering techniques to better understand businesses and their customers. As a leader at ArK we want you to help us define what’s possible and work on what’s valuable.
At ArK you will be a part of our tech and analytics teams and work with data engineers, data scientists, UX designers, data analysts and other ML professionals — bringing your unique skills to the table.

You are …
… Someone who wants to lead and run Machine Learning projects from data crunching and prototyping — to quality assured models that run in a production environment.
… Knowledgeable in the inner workings of the models you apply, and how to construct and optimise for suitable loss functions — and other similar concepts
… Driven by impact and can deliver business value from projects fast, and then iterate over time to increase that value further
… Interested both in the modelling and the engineering aspects of building good ML that works reliably
… A future or current leader in the space who stays up to date and are not afraid to deploy modern techniques, and mentor and knowledge share with colleagues

Nice-to-have
Experience from a product centric company
Product and/or people leadership/management experience
Experience writing blogs or articles, we really want to give back to the community and share our work and findings

More about who we are at ArK
ArK was founded in 2021 by a six-time entrepreneur, a world-class AI technology developer and a veteran banker. Since then we’ve carefully grown our team to 30 - all pitching in with their experience to build something that none of us has seen before.
We believe that the key to a great team culture is great people having a great time together. Our team is one to be part of for the long run, because you won’t want to leave. Our unique combination of startup mentality, experienced team and ambitious vision make ample room for possibilities to grow.
ArK is headquartered in Stockholm but we balance our time between being at the office and working remotely.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
Vi startade Signific för att kunna lösa världens mest spännande och utmanande problem. Det gör vi genom att hjälpa organisationer och team att samla in, strukturera upp och agera på insikter från stora mängder kvantitativ data. På så sätt lär de sig snabbare om hur nytta, förändring och effekt skapas.
Signific jobbar med datadrivna, vassa och nyfikna kunder som t.ex. Detectify, Transfer Galaxy, M och SVT.
Som Machine learning-konsult på Signific hjälper du våra uppdragsgivare att ta sin data till nya, datadrivna nivåer. Din förståelse för både affärs- och datamodeller kombinerat med analys och kod är superviktig för ett datadrivet, lärande arbetssätt. På Signific får du använda dina skills på stora, inspirerande problem.
Utöver att göra skillnad i dina uppdrag är du en stor del av ett framåtlutat bolag som sätter våra anställda i fokus. Vi är ett litet, flexibelt bolag med stora ambitioner och vill ha med dig på resan dit.
Vad du kommer få göra
Vi tror på en öppen approach till lösningar på våra kunders utmaningar. Vi väljer lösning efter problem och inte vice versa. Din roll kan därför variera beroende på ditt intresse och kundernas problem.
Som ML Engineer hos oss ser vi dig troligen göra några av följande saker:
Först och främst hjälpa företag skapa mer nytta av sin data
Ta komplex data till modeller och analyser som löser viktiga verksamhets- och samhällsproblem
Designa, bygga och förfina machine learning i produktion för spännande kunder
Ta fram modeller för stora mängder användardata för att driva produkt- och designbeslut
Ha en nyckelroll att förflytta team och organisationer mot ett datadrivet arbetssätt.
Få ta del av och bidra till kunskapsdelning och nyskapande kultur ihop med dina kollegor
Utvecklas åt det håll du vill
Vem vi tror du är
Vi tror på att bygga ett bolag av olika personer som på olika sätt bidrar till att vi alla trivs och lyckas. För att du ska trivas hos oss och i din roll tror vi dock att det finns några saker som du checkar av merparten av:
Som person
Ser positivt på utmaningar
Gillar att vara självgående men också att samarbeta
Nyfiken på nya teknologier och problem
Vill vara så bra som möjligt på det du gör
Gillar att bidra till kulturen bland dina kollegor och/eller kunskapsdela
I din roll
Är genuint intresserad av att lösa kunders verksamhetsproblem
Har minst 2 års arbetslivserfarenhet inom rollen eller liknande roller
Känner dig riktigt bekväm inom minst ett programmeringsspråk (t.ex. Scala, Python/Pandas eller R)
Har erfarenhet och intresse för att produktionsätta ML-algoritmer
Förstår vilka mått och mätetal som är viktiga för digitala produkter
Gillar och förstår statistik (som t.ex. A/B-tester, signfikanstester och regressionsmodellering)
Noggrann men också lösningsorienterad
Trivs att jobba i agila team och kanske också i en mer ledande roll.
Har stort intresse för Data Engineering/Science/Analytics i allmänhet
Högskoleutbildning är inget krav, men konkret arbetslivserfarenhet är det.
En spännande resa där du får vara med och påverka
Vi är ett nystartat litet bolag, med ambitioner att göra stort avtryck i våra uppdrag och på längre sikt. Vi vill skapa en samling av dom bästa inom vår nisch och bygga en stark kultur av gemenskap, ambition och kunskap. Något som gör en signifikant skillnad helt enkelt.
Hos oss får du
Utmanande uppdrag inom områden du är intresserad av
Kollegor som ser möjligheter och värdet med din kunskap inom data
Vassa kollegor som gillar att lära och läras av varandra
Konkurrenskraftiga förmåner
Inkluderande och hållbar arbetsmiljö
Vill du vara med och göra skillnad?

Title: Deep Learning Engineer
Description:
Be visionary
At Teledyne FLIR, we have a simple but ambitious mission: to develop market-leading thermal and sensing technologies which enhance everyday life. From saving energy, to saving lives Teledyne FLIR is making a real difference in our world.

Our products are used in a wide array of situations to rescue people in danger, detect criminals, conserve energy, navigate safely, provide security around the globe, and protect our environment.
We are looking for individuals who thrive on making an impact and want the excitement of being on a team that wins.

Job Description

Be Visionary
At FLIR, we have a simple but ambitious mission: to develop market-leading thermal and sensing technologies that enhance everyday life. From saving energy to saving lives, FLIR is making a real difference in our world.
Our products are used in a wide array of situations to rescue people in danger, detect criminals, conserve energy, navigate safely, provide security around the globe, and protect our environment.
We are looking for individuals who thrive on making an impact and want the excitement of being on a team that wins.
Job Description
For our Intelligent Transportation Systems (ITS) R&D team in Kortrijk (Belgium) (or Täby – Sweden) we are looking for a creative, passionate and hands-on Senior Machine Learning Engineer with a solid background in AI for object detection & classification solution on the edge. You will be part of a team that is responsible to design and learn convolutional neural networks for visual and infrared sensors for different businesses.
Responsibility
Create more efficient object detection and classification models for different businesses
In collaboration with other colleagues, develop and implement advanced algorithms on embedded camera’s
Responsible to evaluate the performance of implemented algorithms
Following the state of the art in the field of computer vision
Documenting and share the knowledge along the international AI team
Candidate Profile
You are passionate about Computer Vision, Image Processing , Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning.
You have a degree (master or PhD) in Computer Science, Applied Mathematics or other related field and/or specific training
Experience with programming in C++ / python is a plus
Experience with object-oriented design methodology and concepts is a plus
Must be a results-oriented professional with solid organizational and time management skills
What FLIR offers you
To be a part of a market leader company with a 50 years track record
At FLIR, you get a unique opportunity to experience how cutting edge R&D, software- and hardware development come together under one roof. We do our own research, our own development, and our own manufacturing
Permanent employment
Friendly culture with a focus on collaboration, problem-solving and creativity
Fair compensation structure and benefits
Interested?
If you liked what you just read, and believe you are the person that will make us better, do not hesitate to apply.
The selection process is ongoing, so don't wait. When applying, make it easy for yourself. Add a resume and fill out the required fields, no need to add anything else at this point. We accept applications in English.

Teledyne FLIR and all of our employees are committed to conducting business with the highest ethical standards. We require all employees to comply with all applicable laws, regulations, rules and regulatory orders. Our reputation for honesty, integrity and high ethics is as important to us as our reputation for making innovative sensing solutions.
Teledyne FLIR is an equal opportunity employer.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.
For further information see www.babyshop.com
ABOUT THE POSITION
Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.
WHAT YOU'LL DO
Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE
You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...
Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.
Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!
Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Experienced Data Scientist/ Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
Lockas du av en roll där du får möjlighet att bistå uppdragsgivare med datadriven affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling hela vägen från strategiska vägval till implementerad lösning och realiserad nytta? I din roll som ML Engineer kommer du med hjälp av data och maskininlärning ta våra kunder in i framtiden.
Om rollen:
Vår utgångspunkt är alltid i verksamhetsfrågorna och du kommer att vara en nyckelspelare i hela kedjan från Data Engineering, via Data Science-modeller, till produktionsättning och modellförvaltning. Dessutom kommer du ofta att inkluderas i projektens tidigare faser; från affärs- och dataförståelse till data science-prototyper.
Tillämpningsområdet är brett; från att göra prognoser på antal besökare till nöjesparker till att varna för anomalier i fakturor och optimera direktreklam. Vad gäller Machine Learning Engineering så har vi stort fokus på Databricks och jobbar i första hand med molntjänsterna Azure, AWS och Google Cloud Platform.
Mer om oss:
Capgemini, Insights & Data, är Nordens riktmärke inom Data, AI och Analytics. Vi är över 300 anställda, fördelade på våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö och Helsingborg. Våra tjänster inkluderar konsultverksamhet inom Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services och Solution Services. Många av marknadens främsta experter arbetar med oss, vilket sätter oss i bästa möjliga position att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas i sin resa mot datadrivna beslut. Vår storlek på den nordiska marknaden ger oss kompetens och kapacitet att verkligen göra skillnad för våra kunder, och erbjuda alltifrån lokala projekt till större globala utrullningar.
Vem du är:
Flerårig erfarenhet i rollen som Data Scientist/ ML Engineer
Goda kunskaper i Python och tillämpning av Dataanalys och Machine Learning i Python med relevanta paket (ex. Pandas, scikit, pytorch)
Du har en pedagogisk förmåga och kan förklara Data Science på ett lättbegripligt sätt
Akademisk bakgrund inom matematik/ingenjör/IT med inriktning mot data eller har en bakgrund som mjukvaruutvecklare som har gått mot Data Science
Goda kunskaper i såväl svenska som engelska
Meriterande erfarenhet:
Databricks
Förståelse för livscykeln för Data Science-lösningar; från idé till produktionsatta modeller i drift
Produktionssättning av Machine Learning-lösningar och verktyg för MLOps (CI/CD och continious training) i Azure, AWS och/eller Google Cloud Platform
Använt mjukvaruutvecklingsverktyg som Docker för att paketera lösningar i stabila miljöer
Förståelse för övergripande plattformar och arkitektfrågor
Bra affärsförståelse, då du behöver kunna förstå våra uppdragsgivares utmaningar, inte bara de tekniska utmaningarna
Kunskaper om kringliggande fält, som Data Engineering och Business Intelligence
Som person är du driven, verksamhetsorienterad och du trivs lika bra med att arbeta självständigt som i grupp. Du sätter stort fokus på dialogen med kund, men är även intresserad av att engagera dig i att utveckla oss till att bli en ännu bättre arbetsplats. Det är viktigt att du är analytisk, lösningsorienterad och nyfiken, har en god samarbetsförmåga och lätt för att kommunicera. Därtill är det meriterande om du har erfarenhet av eller intresse för att hålla utbildningar och workshops. Det är viktigt att du behärskar svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift eftersom vi har en nära dialog med våra kunder.

Title: Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
We are looking for a Senior ML Engineer to join our team in Indivd.
Responsibilities:
You will work in an experienced team in delivering better deep learning models for computer vision, optimise the cloud GPU deployment and designing meaningful insights together with the end-users. We expect you to have several years of experience with several computer vision projects in your portfolio.
Requirements:
C++
Excellent knowledge of PyTorch/TensorFlow
Rich experience in Computer Vision
Deep Learning
Machine Learning
Statistics
Python
Upper-intermediate English
Will be a plus:
TensorRT
DeepStream
Facial Recognition
Object Detection/tracking
Conditions:
We can offer excellent salary, company laptop, freedom to work in an office or remotely and follow an exciting development together with some of the world's leading experts, entrepreneurs and investors. Generous options programmes are available for key employees.

Title: Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
SENIOR MACHINE LEARNING ENGINEER

As a member of the ML-team you will be working with a broad range of problems with one common denominator – ML will be the key ingredient. As a senior you will be responsible for team success.
As a senior you work to engage clients and team from early idea phase to execution. We believe you have a track record of successfully developing en-to-end ML products, leading teams in commercial as well as delivery settings. We also see that you have passion for ML and opinions on how succeed in applied ML. For us a lead is not a formal title, rather a responsibility to help others to be even more successful. You will also be part of developing Modulai.

You will have to analyze the problem at hand, come up with a solution strategy and execute on it. This typically entails gaining an in-depth understanding of the challenge, understanding the available data, and then re-formulating it as an ML problem. It requires openness, creativity, and an eagerness to learn new methodology and explore new terrains.
We approach these problems as a team where great leaders are essential, meaning that you will have to be able to clearly explain your reasoning and code in order to engage the team as well as clients, investors, and others.

Responsibilities

Helping the team to succeed
Identifying and executing on opportunities (new business, new products)
Challenge and inspire the team in state of the art applied ML
Analyzing and planning problem, solution, and delivery
Preprocessing, feature engineering, and dataset creation
ML model development
Validation of results
Data pipelining and infrastructure development

Our Stack

Python – standard open-source libraries
Scikit-learn and various specialized Python and R ML libraries
Deep learning frameworks such as Pytorch and Tensorflow/Keras
Cloud platforms such as GCP, AWS, Azure
Relational database management systems
Distributed processing such as Apache Spark

Background & Skills

MSc or Ph.D. in a quantitative field
Experience from leading end-to-end ML projects
Excellent communicator (IRL, blog, events etc)
Excellent understanding of a broad set of ML algorithms and frameworks
A passion for lean, clean, and maintainable code
The desire to grow and to share insights with others

Helpful knowledge & Experience

Leadership in fast-growing organisations
Product experience from idea to MVP and monetization.
Deep learning frameworks and theory
Data pipelining and infrastructure
DevOps experience, CI/CD, Kubernetes

About Team Modulai

At Modulai we focus 100% on solving problems with machine learning (ML). We work in teams on a project basis. We work for clients, as part of the core team in startups where we have long-time engagement as well as building our own ML products.
Learning and teamwork are central to how we work. Everyone in the team is or will soon be a full-stack ML engineer with capable scoping and developing end-to-end ML solutions. You should be able to do end-to-end machine learning products by yourself but actually, never do it because we always work in teams. If there is data, we will do ML on it!

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
If you are an Amazing Engineer who wants to get great experiences and make good money while working at a fantastic company, then keep reading!
We are on a mission to enable the A.I. & Data-driven world. Having successfully built up multiple large A.I. teams in several large organizations, it is now the time to build a business around it.
We know how great looks like, and we believe there are recipes and blueprints to get there. We don't just want to build another consultancy; we want to create repeatable patterns and advise companies on the best path forward.
The job is to work as an engineer hands-on in customer projects. We want to be able to provide the best-in-class services together with thought leadership. So we don't just do what our customers ask; we go beyond that and show them how.
We want to build a community where we establish best practices and learn from each other. The technology landscape is moving so fast that we constantly need to update our skills. So it is more critical for us to handle your ongoing development rather than that you know everything from the start.

Your profile;
Education in relevant field (BsC|MsC in Computer engineering/Science or similar)
Background in cloud engineering (AWS, GCP, Azure)
Hands-on experience in architecting AI/Machine Learning Platforms
Wizard when it comes to coding solutions
Experienced with both new and old product offerings (Teradata, Netezza, Snowflake, Databricks, etc.)
Currently, we are now looking for people with extensive experience on Azure.
So what are we offering;
Being a part of building up an advisory company
Competitive base salary
High bonus based on performance
Opportunity to become an owner
Flexibility - Work from anywhere or anytime
Exposure to the latest tech and the possibility to drive through leadership

P.S. - Share this! Don't be afraid that a co-worker or friend will steal this opportunity. If we find multiple talented people, we will open more positions.

Title: Principal Machine Learning Engineer | AI Center of Excellence
Description:
Craft:
Technology & Development
Job Description:
Principal Machine Learning Engineer | AI Center of Excellence
This role is available in either of our sweet locations in:
London
Stockholm
Do you have a dynamic approach to solving problems and processing data at scale? Are you passionate about building machine learning (ML) tools for data scientists? Do you believe machine learning (ML) can have a material impact on how we do business and want to be a part of the journey to help teams, company- wide, enhance our players’ experiences? Then you could be our new, shiny, Principal ML Engineer!
Your role within our Kingdom
You´ll be part of the AI Center of Excellence (ACE) team at King, working closely together with ML Engineers, ML Research Engineers and Data Scientists. Our mission? Discover potential ML use cases across the company, build data models & pipelines, ML models & infrastructure, provide ML use case services to our games reliably and at scale.
As ML Engineer at King, you will be using the latest technologies to build ML products that democratize ML model training, tuning and deployment across the company. With over 250+ million monthly active users and 50 billion events being uploaded daily, it’s key that you care about writing highly optimized code and care about quality. You’ll be working with both streaming as well as batch data in a highly challenging technical environment.
You will work in collaboration with business stakeholders, both within your team and supporting other teams, on creating value from data. Together with your team members you´ll get to learn on the job every day!
Skills to create thrills
So what about you? You have hands- on experience in various ML projects working as an experienced ML engineer. You are a strong advocate for best practices in ML solutions and you have good intuition on what ML models might be most effective and efficient. You are a technical leader, meaning you will be responsible for developing and evolving the solutions fitting the use cases.
Minimum Requirements:
MS or PhD in Computer Science/Engineering, Machine Learning, Data Science, Physics, Mathematics, or other engineering/scientific areas with 5+ years of experience.
Extensive experience working in applied AI/ML and Data Science projects
Deep knowledge and extensive experience with data science and machine learning concepts and algorithms
Experience in distributed data processing and modeling (batch & streaming)
Experience building data pipelines and ML pipelines
Experience in GCP data products (BigQuery, Cloud Storage, Dataflow, Pub/Sub to name a few)
Must be a tenacious and self- catalyzing problem solver. Must be able to synthesize disparate data, detect and work around broken data, and investigate every possibility until you are confident you have and understand a thorough solution
Process- oriented driving toward visibility, accountability, and communication
Team- oriented, ability to build long- lasting and collaborative relationships effectively. You work selflessly and enthusiastically, serving as a positive catalyst for collaborative solutioning
You contribute to the expertise in every data and analytic conversation as well as you listen with openness to other’s expertise
A passion for analytics and diving into as well as experiencing the products on which you work (video game enthusiasm with a solid understanding of the connection of gameplay to spending behavior is a plus)
Ability to adapt quickly, high tolerance for ambiguity, and ability to coordinate on a team
Tasty bonus skills
Have any sweet experience with one or some of the following areas? Then we sure like to hear about them!
Development in or exposure to environments/software products in Python and Java
Experience working with Tensorflow, Pytorch, Flink, Kafka, Spark or similar
Contributions to open source projects
We know that you are into games on some level (casual, console, board- games, Uno etc.)
Buzz: Data Modeling, Programmer, ML Engineer, Gaming, GCP, Platforms, AI, ML, TDD, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Research and development, Data Science
About King
King is the game developer behind the world- famous Candy Crush franchise, as well as mobile game hits including Farm Heroes, Bubble Witch and Pet Rescue. Candy Crush is the top- grossing franchise in US app stores, a position it has held for the last two years, and King’s games are being played by 245 million monthly active users as of Q3 2021. King, which is part of the Activision Blizzard group since its acquisition in 2016, employs nearly 2,000 people in game studios in Stockholm, Malmö, London, Barcelona and Berlin, and offices in San Francisco, New York, and Malta.
A Great Saga Needs All Sorts of Heroes
Making games is fun. Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply cannot expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes.
Making the World Playful
Making the World Playful is what inspires us to create new experiences and raise the bar. It’s what makes King a place where we can all dream bigger, continue to add innovation to our games, broadening the portfolio and exploring new territories in mid- core and casual. We take the art and science of gaming to the next level through our curiosity for the unexplored, passion for games, respect for each other and love for our players - and we’re not afraid to have fun along the way. In fact, together with our parent company Activision Blizzard and experts around the world, we believe having fun is good for you. There has never been a better time to join us. We're dreaming bigger and see a world of possibilities ahead. If you share our passion, our values, and our hunger to shape the future, join us in Making the World Playful!
Applications need to be in English.
Discover King at careers.king.com

Title: Machine Learning hjälte sökes!
Description:
Vill du arbeta i en idérik miljö med fantastiska och prestigelösa kollegor som skapar smarta lösningar till den livsviktiga livsmedelsindustrin?
Vill du veta mer? Det hoppas vi..
Om tjänsten
Hej potentiella nya kollega! Om du börjar hos oss så kommer du att få arbeta i en agil modern organisation, där teamwork och kunden står i fokus.

Våra kunder är några av skandinaviens största livsmedelsföretag och våra projekt är roliga, utmanande och leder alltid till en förbättring på något sätt. Är du nyfiken på vad vi har förbättrat hittills? Vi har minskat matsvinn hos en kund och hos en annan har vi analyserat data från mjölkkornas mjölk för att korna ska må bättre.
Du blir..
..en del av vår familj och välkomnas till en arbetsplats där alla ser fram emot att gå till jobbet för vi har kul ihop, hjälper varandra framåt och är prestigelösa. Vi ligger på en 5:e plats på Great Place to Work listan och vi är ett jämställt gäng med 45% kvinnor och 55% män. Vi har högt till tak och nära till beslut, där vi värnar om vår personal. Hos oss får du möjligheten att arbeta med utvecklande och varierande uppdrag i en framtidsbransch. Du får en bra start hos oss med en mentor som hjälper dig att komma in i arbetet och ett genomarbetat onboardingprogram.

Om dig
Du är en nyfiken person som trivs med att finna lösningar, vågar göra fel och du är omtänksam och delar gärna med dig av kunskaper och erfarenheter för att öka ditt teams kunskaper. Du har tidigare erfarenhet från konsultrollen och gillar att ha kundkontakt. När det är mycket att göra så tappar du inte fokus och du ber om hjälp om du behöver. Du som alla andra vänner i teamet gillar teknik och utveckling och att kommunicera med kunder på svenska och engelska är inga problem för dig.
Din kompetens

Vi söker dig som vill hjälpa livsmedelsindustrin att klara av tuffare tider med höjda energipriser och inflation. Du har tidigare erfarenhet av att ha jobbat som Machine Learning Engineer, gärna i konsultform och du har inga problem att sälja in bra lösningar. Du kommer att arbeta i team som självständigt, i ett agilt mindset.
Vi ser gärna att du har kunskap inom:
Python
Azure- eller AWS ML tjänster såsom Tenserflow.
Men andra Machine learning verktyg är också intressanta
Om oss
Elvenite levererar hållbara lösningar för framtidens livsmedelsindustri. Mitt i hjärtat hos några av Skandinaviens ledande livsmedelsföretag kombinerar vi djupt bransch- och verksamhetskunnande med målet att maximera värdet av deras affärssystem och processer. Vi erbjuder dataanalyser och skapar datadrivna insikter och innovation, enkelt sagt, "vi gillar att göra livsmedelsindustrin smartare".
Vi söker dig som gör det du tror på, och är bra på det. Du är nyfiken, redo att utvecklas, vågar göra misstag och du har passion för att skapa förbättringar. Ta chansen och utvecklas med oss!
Det praktiska
1. Vi hoppas att du vill jobba på något av våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg eller Malmö
2. Arbetstid = 100%
3. Vi har fina förmåner och individuella löner
4. Vi vill ha dig så snart som möjligt eller efter årsskiftet.
Sista ansökningsdag 21 December

Vid frågor kontakta therese.gawor@elvenite.se

Title: Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD
Description:
Join us on our journey to net zero. We are looking for a Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD to join our R&D team.

At Aurobay, we are re-imagining motion for a brighter tomorrow. That means challenging accepted beliefs and pushing the boundaries of what you’ve done before. But you won’t have to do it alone. You’ll be working alongside fantastic people who are caring and collaborative, with a global mindset, and a commitment to creating excellence.

Do you fit the profile?
As a Machine Learning Engineer, you’ll be helping to shape the future of sustainable powertrain development. Our team currently consists of six data scientists, SW engineers, and model-based calibration engineers. We develop new methods for measurement data collection and analysis to help R&D become more efficient and data driven. We also work closely with other advanced engineering teams.

You will use the data we are collecting in our rigs to build models for predicting engine emissions of hazardous species. The models can be used both offline in the development phase, and on the edge for On-Board Monitoring (OBM) and On-Board Diagnostics (OBD) in our customer vehicles. As part of this job, you’ll have the opportunity develop your own machine-learning projects together with the rest of the team. We give our engineers the freedom and time for their own projects, to try out new ideas and fine-tune their skills.

You will also:
Train and evaluate ML models for predicting emissions
Work closely together with subject matter experts to align data/measurement requirements and incorporate physical models into the model
Optimize algorithm memory and CPU load for predictions on the edge together with function developers
What we offer

Although we are proud of our heritage at Volvo Cars and Geely, this is a start-up environment, where you’ll be helping to create the Aurobay of tomorrow. You’ll get plenty of both formal and informal opportunities for learning and development. Joining Aurobay will give you a platform for personal and professional development, and a springboard for your future career.

What you’ll get

We’re passionate about sharing our success and making sure you’re well rewarded, from pay and bonuses to the company pension. Our benefits are designed to improve your life at work and at home, with health and wellbeing support, life and travel insurance, and a timebank you can use to flex your work-life balance:

Competitive salary
Wellness contribution of up to SEK 5 000/year
A personal and professional development scheme to support your growth.
Want to drive a car? - Discount to buy a car, and a competitive leasing cost for a company car.
Additional pension funding.
Competitive additional and full-cover insurance.
Other benefits through an industry-leading portal: health and wellness, bicycle, electronics, shopping, to name a few.
What you’ll need

A master’s degree or higher in data science, mathematics, statistics, physics or relevant fields.
Strong programming skills in Python, Julia, or MATLAB.
Experience in ML algorithms such as linear regression, artificial neural networks, and boosted decision tree regression.
Nice to have experience in

Time series modeling, especially ML algorithms that can be used for time series such as recurrent neural networks, convolutional neural networks, or transformers
Internal Combustion Engines
Chemical models for catalytic converters
Embedded systems
We encourage diversity and believe that the different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives our people bring make us stronger as a company.

Questions

If you have any additional questions regarding the position, you are welcome to contact recruiting manager Erik Fyrk, erik.fyrk@aurobay.com

For questions regarding the recruitment process please contact Recruiter Felicia Eriksson, felicia.eriksson@aurobay.com

Unionen: Ordf Joakim Dahlin, joakim.dahlin@volvocars.com, tel +46734630172

Ledarna: Ordf Håkan Modigh, hakan.modigh@volvocars.com, tel +46733333801

Akademikerna: Ordf. Henrik Simonsen, henrik.simonsen@aurobay.com, tel +46708219331

How to apply

Deadline to submit your application is 31st of January, but the selection process will be running continuously. Please note that due to GDPR, we do not accept applications via email.
Good luck with your application!

Title: Machine Learning Engineer to Livewrapped
Description:
Livewrapped is an Ad Tech company that provides a service to their customers to help maximize their digital ad revenue on different websites through Header Bidding. Due to a large expansion Livewrapped is now looking for a new colleague.
About the role:
As a Machine Learning Engineer at Livewrapped you will have the overall responsibility to develop their product where Machine Learning and other optimization techniques are applicable. You will create and develop optimization models in order to maximize revenue for publishers.
Your tasks will be to optimize parameters used in online real-time auctions using non-personalized data collected from, for instance, a user's browser and the performance of participating bidders in said auctions.

Who are we looking for?
You have a solid background in Machine Learning and you enjoy solving complex optimization problems independently, as well as being able to implement your solutions. You are able to share your knowledge and ideas with your colleagues.
A minimum of 4 years experience in Machine Learning and optimization techniques
Ability to write the code needed to implement optimization techniques
Knowledge within C# programming language
Fluent in English, both writing and speaking
It is an advantage if you have:
Experience within Ad-tech
Relevant University degree or education
In this recruitment process we are working with Wise IT. If you want to know more about the position please reach out to recruitment consultant Jacob at jacob.elmeljung@wiseit.se or +46 76-000 1840.

About us

Livewrapped is a technology company specializing in assisting publishers to increase their digital advertising revenue through so-called Header Bidding. Since the start in 2017, the company has quickly managed to establish itself as one of the leading players in the Nordic market, despite fierce competition from large international companies with competing products.

Title: ML Engineer
Description:
We’re looking for a curious Machine learning engineer to join our small team and make Kive an indispensable tool for every creative in the world. We care deeply about user experience and ease of use, and put significant focus on top-notch UI and interactions.

The data team at Kive
The role of the team is to help other teams leverage data to build a better product for our users and help grow our business. Initially you would be expected to work broadly, but as the team and Kive grows there will be potential to go deeper in areas based on interest. You would formally be part of the data team, but would work very closely with tech and other Kive teams to deliver successful projects.

We’re on a mission to make the world more creative and creativity more collaborative.

We genuinely believe that when creativity and technology come together, something close to magic happens. In our opinion, the intersection of creativity and tech is the most exciting space to work in – one that pushes culture and imagination forward.
In this role you will
Design, build, ship, evaluate and refine ML projects in close collaboration with developers and others at Kive

Shape and set up systems, infrastructure, tools and processes for running, training, deploying models in a way that allow us to move fast with confidence

Build and maintain data pipelines for collecting, processing and egesting data needed for your models

Continuously think about and implement ways to improve the productivity of yourself, others at Kive. Always leave Kive’s processes and infra in a slightly better way than you found them

Work with different kinds of data (i.e. image, video, tabular) on a broad range of problems

Not have all tools, data and processes served on a platter. You will instead have to make things happen and set things up together with the rest of us at Kive
What we offer
Competitive salary and an attractive equity program in a start-up funded by top investors Creandum (1st investor Spotify, iZettle, depop) and EQT Ventures (Einride, Sonantic).
An opportunity to join an early-stage company and influence how we build the company before there are too many processes and structures in place.
A learning environment, with interesting challenges to solve and an ambitious team to support you.
A flexible work setup – work from home or join us in the office located in the heart of Stockholm.
Work in an organisation where data is not an afterthought and a “side interest” but something that is there and has a seat at the table from the start.

You will work in an organisation where the founder is highly driven by data and encourages it being used across the organisation.
You'll be a great fit if
Worked in similar role and start up, early stage company for 4+ years

Are curious about how data, creatives and creativity can interact today and in the future.

Business oriented - You are more motivated by delivering tangible value to our users than increasing precision of your model by another decimal point

Like working in a collaborative setting - believe successful data projects is a team sport that requires collaboration across multiple teams

Familiarity with pytorch/tensorflow, bigquery/snowflake, dataform/dbt, beam/spark, airflow/dagster/kubeflow/TFX/Vertex AI

Familiarity with developer tools and processes (i.e. git, peer reviews, CI/CD, unit testing, terraform/pulumi, Docker)

Believe simple is good - if an easy solution to a hard problem exists use that solution and move on to the next problem (there are many where you are needed)
Perks and Benefits
‍
Business co-ownership
️
Fitness stipend
‍
Remote friendly

No qualifying days
‍
Personal learning budget

Catered breakfast

Swap public holidays

Celebration
️
6 weeks paid vacation

The tools you need

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.

For further information see www.babyshop.com

ABOUT THE POSITION

Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO

Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE

You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...

Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE

The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.

Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!

Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Global companies and governmental entities rely on us to solve their most complex data challenges. Our employees collaborate to reduce risks and create opportunities for customers in more than 100 countries. We’re adaptable, curious and ambitious. That’s why here, you’ll have the freedom to drive change, the trust to find your own path, and the space to explore more.
Machine Learning Engineer/Data Scientist
From our research and engineering teams in Sweden and Germany to our sales, business and marketing offices around the world, BehavioSec is committed to making a better, more secure internet. Our company is always looking for enthusiastic, committed and smart people. As a member of our team, you’ll be contributing to a total rethink of how companies secure experiences for customers and users around the world to reduce fraud.
THE PROBLEMS
BehavioSec power real-time analyzing of behavioral data for Fraud prevention and authentication. We analyze data collected from the user and validates it against a stored profile for that user and calculates a risk of fraudulent usage for the session.
RESPONSIBILITIES
Work with a team with different backgrounds to frame problems, both mathematically and business wise.
Perform exploratory data analysis to gain a deeper understanding of the problem.
Construct and fit statistical, machine learning, or optimization models
Write production modeling code; collaborate with Software Engineers to implement algorithms in production
Analyze and Visualize findings and data to further enhance the product.
EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS
M.S. or Ph.D. in Statistics, Operations Research, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering Physics or another quantitative field.
Passion for solving unstructured and non-standard mathematical problems.
End-to-end experience with data, including querying, aggregation, analysis, and visualization.
Proficiency with Python Java or other programming languages.
Willingness to collaborate and communicate with others to solve a problem.
BEING A PART OF THE BEHAVIOSEC TEAM
Have Impact: We take on meaningful and challenging projects that affect fraud prevention on a global scale.
Collaborate: We work internally with people from a variety of backgrounds — such as product teams, engineering teams, sales teams. We also work externally with our customers, often on site, to understand and solve their problems.
Have Independence: We trust each other to effectively manage time and priorities—we don’t micromanage. We want to give people the space to think for themselves.
Grow: We push ourselves and our peers to improve themselves and the world around them.

#LI-Hybrid

Title: Maskininlärningsingenjör
Description:
ACNR växer och vi söker nu en Machine Learning Engineer som vill ingå i vårt lag av kreativa problemlösare. Bolaget präglas av en mogen och hjälpsam kultur där problemlösning alltid är i fokus. Vi arbetar med avancerade projekt där de produkter och koncept vi utvecklar har en genomgående mycket hög komplexitet och med väldigt höga krav på driftsäkerhet.
Vi erbjuder en tekniskt avancerad miljö där vi har tillgång till en mängd maskiner och utrustning vilket ger oss möjligheten att driva en mer forskningsinriktad verksamhet med utgång i reverse engineering, hårdvaruhackning och prototyp- och konceptframtagning.
Vi arbetar med olika kundprojekt kopplat till myndigheter och utvalda industrier där vi ställer höga krav på säkerhet och personlig integritet.

Vad vi söker
Vi söker dig som har en relevant utbildning inom området och som besitter en nyfikenhet och intresse för teknik. Vi ser att du har några års erfarenhet av arbete i Linuxmiljöer samt erfarenhet av att arbeta med ML/DL on the edge (embedded device) då arbetet bland annat innefattar optimering av strömförbrukning och att få ner modeller på targets. Du bör besitta goda kunskaper inom C/C++ och Python och du bör ha erfarenhet av Tensorflow eller PyTorch. Meriterande om du har arbetat med plattformen Jetson samt om du arbetat med databaser och data pipelines.
Vi tror att du har ett stort intresse inom området och vill utforska nya möjligheter, tekniker och verktyg för att alltid hitta den bästa lösningen till problemen vi ställs inför.
Som person bör du vara nyfiken, kreativ med stor personlig mognad och integritet. Vi vill så klart att du värderar lagspel högt för att du ska trivas hos oss.

Hör av dig
Om du tycker rollen och miljön vi kan erbjuda dig låter intressant, hör av dig till Henrik på henrik@acnr.se, eller sök nedan. Vi rekryterar löpande.

Våra befattningar omfattas av vid var tid gällande bestämmelser för säkerhetsskydd. Det innebär att du kan behöva genomgå säkerhetsprövning i enlighet med säkerhetsskyddslagen och med krav på ett svenskt medborgarskap.

Title: Data Scientist med fokus på ML och Big Data till...
Description:

Har du dessutom nedanstående på ditt CV, då ska du passa på att söka till denna tjänst!

Vi söker dig som har:

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About the company
This is a well known Swedish car manufacturer which is also Sweden's largest company. Their founding home is located in Eskilstuna where their factory is specialized in the production of components with transmissions and axels for wheel loaders and articulated haulers. Here work the teams who work across functions including Technology, Sales & Marketing, IT and Purchasing, employing over 2,100 people.
The recruiter will provide you with more information about this company during a phone interview.

Your role
The background to this need is that there is a product / application which is going to be transformed into several new connected services. In your role as a Data Analyst your responisbility will be to coordinate and support the maintenance work of the digital product / application. You will also participate and drive analytics explorations, mainly in the connected service domain.
Main tasks and responsibilities
To coordinate and support the maintenance work of the digital product / application
To learn several activities in the maintenance process
To execute as many of the maintenance tasks as possible
To coordinate a cross-functional team where the historical competence is present
To participate and drive analytics explorations, mainly in the connected service domain
To understand business problems and translating into data and analytics opportunities
To make analysis of connected service data
To work together with Stakeholders, Data Engineers and Data Scientist in explorations


Your qualifications
In this role you have the following qualifications:
At least one work-year of experience in a similar role
Experience and knowledge in exploration mode development and innovation
Experience in analytics tools and techniques, such as SQL, Power BI, Python, Data Bricks

We believe you also have:

Ability to collaborate with different stakeholders
Strong problem solving
Self-propelled and ability to independently drive and solve complex tasks
An analytics mindset, where hands on experience in analytics tools and technologies is a merit

About Clevry
For over 30 years we have been the change maker for a more soft skills driven work-life within talent acquisition, assessments and advisory. We operate globally with customers, consultants and candidates from North America to Singapore with headquarters in Brighton, Stockholm and Helsinki. At Clevry we have over 150 soft skills certified recruiters, business psychologists and experts at your service.

The process
Clevry thinks your soft skills are as important as your hard skills. Do you want to know more about your soft skills and how to optimize them?
As you apply for this position you have the possibility to answer a questionnaire from us about your soft skills. The questionnaire takes approximately 10 minutes to fill out and generates a feedback report (in Swedish) that highlights your soft skills. This report can be used for both personal and professional purposes.
Both questionnaire and feedback report are sent to your e-mail inbox.
We screen candidates continuously and the position could be filled prior to last application date. Does this role sound like a good match? Please apply today.
Follow us on LinkedIn: Clevry Sweden

Title: Nordea is looking for a Data Analyst!
Description:
Do you want to work at one of the leading banks in the Nordic region? We are looking for a Data Analyst for Nordea, a position where you have many opportunities to expand your skills and develop your career. If you have the technical skills necessary and a growth mindset and want to learn, unlearn and re-learn, want to take initiative and accountability for improving your own performance- apply today!
About the role
Nordea is now looking for a Data Analyst to join their team on the business side of the organization. You will be joining a project working on resolution reporting and working closely together with the analytics team. You will be joining a senior team which will enable an in-depth learning process.
Nordea is creating an agile environment where they experiment and grow together – and they need your ideas and unique background. With Nordea, you will be in good company with a chance to make your mark on something bigger. This is a long-term assignment through Academic Work with the possibility to be directly recruited by Nordea if everyone is happy with the collaboration.
You are offered
To become part of a large international company at the forefront
The opportunity to develop internally and increase your expertise
As a consultant for Academic Work, we offer great opportunities for you to grow professionally, build your network and create valuable contacts for the future. Read more about our consulting offer.
Job duties
Analyze large amounts of high-resolution data across several database systems used by various regulatory reporting frameworks
Build new scripts for process automation
Develop SME knowledge in a regulatory domain (e.g. ESG, Resolution Reporting)
Understand the impact of new regulations and/or new business initiatives on regulatory processes and data
Present findings, share insights with colleagues, managers and other stakeholders.
We are looking for
Have a Bachelor's or Master's degree in science, technology, engineering, maths, finance or similar
Fluent in English in both speech and writing as it is used in daily work
At least about one year of experience working in either of: Python, R, SQL and strong interest and ability to learn tools for data analytics.
When applying, please share your GitHub link or projects that are showing you skills within Python, R, or SQL.
It is meritorious if you have
Experience working within the finance field
Experience working with large data (over a few million rows)
SME (subject matter expert) knowledge in a regulatory domain
As a person you are
Communicative
Analytical
Fearless
Besides this we see that the right person for the job has:
Natural curiosity, likes picking things apart, analyzing and questioning things, and enjoying figuring out a better way. Furthermore, we believe you are keen to stick longer with problems and deep-dive into challenges. You also show good judgment, think ahead and prioritize work tasks appropriately. We also see that you have the ability to connect the dots – zoom-in & out of details, step-in & out of scenarios, seek and put together pieces, and play detective when needed.
Övrig information
Start: Soon as possible
Work extent: Full Time
Location: Stockholm Office, possibility to work remote 2 days a week.
The recruitment process is handled by Academic Work and all questions regarding the position are handled by Academic Work. For this position, you will be requested to do a logical test and a background check on your criminal records.
Client information
Nordeais a leading Nordic universal bank. They have helpt customers realize their dreams and aspirations – and have done so for 200 years.

Description:
Resource to work a primary point of contact for analytical tasks for one of the product teams. Will work alongside 3 other data analysts, one of which is senior, to support the success of app feature and product development.
