Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Company Description

Vattenfall is one of Europe’s largest producers and retailers of electricity and heat. Our main markets are Sweden, Germany, the Netherlands, Denmark, and the UK. The Vattenfall Group has approximately 20,000 employees. We have been electrifying industries, powering homes and transforming life through innovation for more than 100 years. We now want to make fossil free living possible within one generation and we are driving the transition to a sustainable energy system.
Vattenfall Consumer Sales Nordic is responsible for the electricity contracts for households and small enterprises in the Nordic Region. We are a part of BA Customers & Solutions which also includes E-Mobility and Decentralized Energy Solutions such as solar panels. Our organization is fully agile and consists of several cross-functional business teams and specialized enablement teams.

Job Description

Vattenfall Consumer Sales Nordic is looking for Data Analyst who has good analytical skills as well as strong customer and business mindset. As a Data Analyst you will transform complex data into usable insights and will use your strong communication skills to advice others and take them to next step of becoming data savvy. You will work closely with sales and marketing experts as well as with other analysts in Helsinki and in Stockholm. We will offer you an exciting and varied job! Your analyses will have a direct impact on how Vattenfall communicates with our customers and markets our products.
Your tasks and responsibilities
Drive data and analytical initiatives in cross-functional teams
Generate data-driven actionable insights from the data
Identify new opportunities within data and analytics
Build new target groups and segmentation for marketing campaigns
Acquire, process, and clean data for analysis and modeling
Create reports and visualizations to track and understand business KPIs and performance
Together with other analysts and IT, maintain and develop our analytical data environment

Qualifications
Relevant university degree
Experience as working with data and analytics, preferably in sales and marketing setting
Comfortable working with large datasets
Proficiency with programming languages such as SQL, Python or R
Knowledge of statistics and modelling
Strong communication skills and an ability to present complex results to a non-tech audience
Experience with modern cloud-based data and analytics solutions (preferably on Microsoft Azure and/or Databricks) is considered an advantage
Experience in data visualization and reporting tools like Power BI is an advantage
Fluency in written and spoken English and Swedish

Additional Information

Our Offer
We offer a challenging and international work environment and the possibility to work with some of the best in the field. You will be working in interdisciplinary teams and you can always count on support from committed colleagues as ‘Ask and Share’ concept is essential for the way we work. We offer attractive employment conditions (smart working, flexible working hours and a good-work-life balance) and opportunities for personal and professional development. Click here for further information.

Location You will be placed in our office in Stockholm (Solna).

For more information about the position you are welcome to contact hiring manager Marjo Kivelä, Chapter lead Analytics, +358 40 628 2082, 7.12 at 13-14 or 19.12 at 13-14.. For more information about the recruitment process you are welcome to contact our recruiter Cecilia Wijkman, cecilia.wijkman@vattenfall.com

Trade Union representatives in Sweden via Vattenfall´s switchboard +46 8 739 50 00. Rolf Olsson (Akademikerna) Cecilia Bodin (Ledarna) Mikael Mukka (SEKO) Jens Morell (Unionen)

We welcome your application in English. We kindly request that you do not send applications by any means other than via our website.

At Vattenfall we are convinced that diversity contributes to build a more profitable and attractive company and we strive to be a good role model regarding diversity. Vattenfall works actively for all employees to have the same opportunities and rights regardless of gender, ethnicity, age, transgender identity or expression, religion or other belief, disability or sexual orientation. Click here for further information.

Since Vattenfall is a part of the Swedish critical infrastructure, many of our services are security classed. If this position is security classed the final candidates might be subjected to a security vetting process, according to the Swedish legislation.

We look forward to receiving your application!

Title: Production Data Analyst [Production Intelligence]
Description:
Job Description

As a Production Data Analyst at Massive, you work with extracting, visualizing, monitoring and analyzing production related data, with the purpose of providing visibility and predictability of our game productions which in turn allows our producers to make data informed decisions, measure progress, mitigate risks, plan ahead and improve the way we make games.
In this role you will work with several different data sources, ranging from HR and financial data to data from our project tracking software, version control software and build pipeline.
As a Production Data Analyst you will work closely with the Production Directors on the game projects, who are the primary customer of this data, understanding their needs and assisting them with interpreting the data and providing them with insights. You will also work closely with Production Transformation, who strives to continuously improve the Studio’s production methods. This position reports directly to the Studio Production Strategy Director.
This is a permanent position based in Malmö Sweden, with the opportunity to work partially from home according to our Flexible Workplace Policy. Please apply in English (our company language), and we’ll check your application asap!
What you’ll do
You implement, visualize, monitor and analyze production data and KPIs, and provide insights and guidance to the production teams based on this data.
Together with the producers on the game projects, identify what KPIs and data visualizations are needed to improve visibility and predictability of the production.
Define how data and insights will be reported and ensure the delivery and relevance of the reporting throughout the production period.
Providing ongoing data informed production risk assessment, flagging trends and KPIs that are off target.
International travel required.

Qualifications

What you’ll bring
You are curious and have a passion for building easily accessible data visualizations that can be intuitively understood. You are well oriented in how software production works, and thrive working close to the daily challenges of production. You have solid communication skills and feel comfortable presenting your findings to an audience, explaining complex information simply and clearly. You are passionate about detail, math, statistics and data technologies. Besides the above we’re looking for someone aligned with our core values and the following skills and experience:
Degree in one of the following areas: Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, Business Analytics, or relevant professional experience
Solid experience in data analytics or business analytics.
You have a passion for detail, math and statistics in general.
Strong communication skills is a must.
Excellent skills with data visualization tools (ex: Tableau, PowerBI)
Proficient in writing complex SQL queries.
Is a bonus if you:
Have previous experience of video game production
Have previous experience of financial analysis

Additional Information

Massive Entertainment is a world-leading AAA studio located in Malmö Sweden and is part of the Ubisoft family. We’re a multinational team of more than 750 passionate and highly skilled people from 50+ different countries. Our studio’s goal has always been – and still is – to craft the finest gaming experiences for all players.
At Massive, you get to do what you love most while bringing your own experience to our ongoing projects, like Tom Clancy’s The Division 2, Avatar: Frontiers of Pandora, and The Star Wars Project. We're also developing new tech here, such as our in-house engine Snowdrop, and Ubisoft Connect - Ubisoft's digital ecosystem and distribution platform.
All your application information will be kept confidential according to EEO & GDPR guidelines.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Som Data Analyst hos oss på Forefront arbetar du tillsammans med andra Frontiers för att hjälpa våra kunder att på ett hållbart sätt lyckas med sin data- och molntransformation. Tillsammans med kunden vill vi göra avtryck och skapa förändring. Våra huvudpartners är Google och Microsoft vilket innebär att du oftast kommer arbeta antingen på Google Cloud Platform eller Azure.

Kvalifikationer

Hos Forefront kan du förvänta dig att du får

Vara en del av ett härligt Analyticsteam och ett företag där vi arbetar tillsammans och levererar i team som bidrar med olika förmågor
Kompentensutvecklas genom utbildningar internt på Forefront, genom certifieringar inom områden du är intresserad av att förbättras inom, samt givetvis via delning av kunskap i våra teamleveranser
Bidra starkt och ta del av andras erfarenheter inom Analytics, samt vara en viktig del i att ligga i teknikens framkant när det gäller att utnyttja ny funktionalitet i de verktyg vi använder för analys och visualisering
Arbeta i en molnbaserad miljö och mot datakällor som kan variera mellan väl strukturerade och förberedda data i datalager, filer i data lakes, API baserade källor, strömmande data eller en kombination av flera av exemplen ovan
Arbeta med många olika kravställare och nyckelpersoner nära våra kunder
Översätta användares krav och behov till lösningar i rapport- och analysverktyg inklusive definiera vilken information som behövs och hur det skall visualiseras
Bidra i informationsmodellering för att på bästa sätt presentera information för användare
Hjälpa kunder ta bättre affärsbeslut genom att göra deras organisation mer datadriven

Vi tror att du behöver dessa färdigheter för att lyckas som Data Analyst hos Forefront

Är vetgirig, nyfiken och har ett driv för att utvecklas exempelvis vilja veta mer om avancerad analys och hur det kan bidra till kunders lösningar
Har lätt för att sätta sig in i kunders verksamhet och deras behov samt brinner för att hjälpa kund skapa bättre nytta av sin information
Bra känsla för hur man ”drar en historia” dvs omvandla data till berättande information genom en kreativ visualiseringsförmåga
Erfarenhet av att arbeta med något analys- och rapportverktyg som ex. Power BI, Looker, Tableau, Google Analytics mfl.

Som en del av Forefront är du en Frontier. Vi Frontiers har passion, vill göra skillnad och bryta ny mark. Våra värderingar är tydliga och styr oss i vardagen såväl som när vi växer. Rätt kompetens är oerhört viktig, men personen bakom dem är och kommer alltid att vara ännu viktigare.

En dynamisk och lättrörlig organisation

Inspirerande och idérika kollegor

Senaste tekniska lösningarna

Närhet till affär och kund

Fokus på kunskapsdelning & kompetensutveckling

Stark gemenskap med många olika sociala nätverk

Tydligt fokus på jämställdhet och mångfald

Ett företag att växa tillsammans med över tid

Work life balance

Om företaget

Forefront Consulting är ett verksamhets- och IT-konsultbolag med drygt 400 anställda. Med kontor på sex orter i Sverige, guidar vi företag och organisationer i det digitala landskapet och övriga transformationer.

Oavsett om uppdraget avser affärsverksamhet, teknologiska plattformar eller designlösningar är utgångspunkten alltid att först skapa en samsyn kring nödvändiga förändringar för att sedan kunna realisera dessa på bästa sätt för avsedd effekt.

Avsikt
Avsikten är motorn i vårt arbete och medvetenheten om var målet ligger. Den ger oss styrkan att ifrågasätta det till synes uppenbara, lägger kraft bakom våra påståenden och motiverar våra beslut.

Avtryck
Avtryck säger något om vår starka ambition att skapa förändring. Att göra verklig skillnad. Både i aktuella kundprojekt och i vår omvärld i stort. Vi är stolta över att våra kunder talar väl om oss. Och vi blir glada när vår verksamhet ses som en positiv förebild av kollegorna i branschen.

Insikt
Det är i insikten som vårt arbete börjar. För att nå dit krävs tålamod, empati och ödmjukhet, samt nyfikenhet nog att kunna ta in flera olika perspektiv och väga samman informationen. Insikt handlar om att verkligen förstå problemet innan vi försöker lösa det.

Tillsammans
Tillsammans är den väg vi väljer för att nå de mål vi siktar mot. Ordet ger uttryck för vårt sökande efter mervärdet i en gemensam strävan. Det handlar om att befinna sig jämsides med kunder och kollegor. Utan prestige och onödiga hierarkier, men med delaktighet, ansvar och arbetsglädje.

Utsikt
Utsikt beskriver både en position och den medvetna ansträngning som är nödvändig för att ta sig dit. Begreppet påminner oss också om att goda rådgivare är öppna och ödmjuka. Det handlar om att se och att särskilja, med fokus på kundens affärsnytta.

Sebastian Ljungberg | Kontaktperson

Skicka email

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
What is ArK?
There are many consumer facing fintech products, but finance as a whole is virtually untouched by technology. Investment decisions are still being made off of pdf’s and “shark tank”-like processes rather than utilising the forecasting methods found at companies like Spotify or Google. This makes capital allocation riddled with bias and very ripe for disruption. At ArK we’re convinced that by putting data and tech at the heart of finance we can impact how money flows and, in turn, create a more democratised and unbiased economy.
Today we offer founders access to our machine learning platform AIM. Through connecting their raw data we can fully understand what they’ve built without any bias; connecting what has been achieved historically into a simulated 5-year future. This prediction is the foundation for the transformational loans that we are able to issue, and a tool that founders get to keep for business optimisation.
ArK was founded in 2021 by a six-time entrepreneur, a world-class AI technology developer and a veteran banker. Since then we’ve carefully grown our team to 30 - all pitching in with their experience to build something that none of us has seen before. ArK is headquartered in Stockholm but we balance our time between being at the office and working remotely.
Data Analyst
As a data analyst at ArK, you will be working closely with our data scientists, commercial teams, engineering and design. Your goal is to ensure we are able to make the best credit decisions in the world, and that we do so in an increasingly scalable and automated way.
Together we build AIM, our analytics platform, that not only helps us develop financial products, but is also turning into an amazing tool for founders of growth companies to use.
In other words, the analysis we do isn’t kept to ourselves, but something we share interactive access to with our customers. Data Analysts at ArK develop the insights that we package there, and the vision is to give its users an unfair competitive advantage.
Who are you?
Someone who enjoys learning new things and tools, and who enjoys pushing themselves and others to grow
You likely have an economics or STEM background, but we really value broad perspectives, so if you come from elsewhere but have an inclination for data, tech or business — you’re more than welcome to apply
A few years hands-on experience with modern data analytics, using tools like SQL, dbt, Python, R and probably some dashboarding solution.
Nice-to-have
A good understanding of statistics and advanced data modelling
Experience running projects and collaborating with external stakeholders
Experience setting up KPIs and understanding their drivers
An interest in business and what makes (some) companies succeed
What’s it like to work at ArK?
We believe that the key to a great team culture is great people having a great time together. Our unique combination of startup mentality, experienced team and ambitious vision make room for possibilities to grow into leadership roles, either going deep into tech or towards people management (or why not both!).

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Background
We are looking for an experienced data analyst with strong technical skills in PowerBI and other dashboard technologies to support an existing product team. You will support in developing metrics from customer acquisition, retention, and market penetration.

BigQuery
PowerBI

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Working at NA-KD is unlike any other fashion gig. We’re a young company with a start-up mentality and (a borderline insane) hunger to be the best. In less than 5 years NA-KD has become one of the fastest growing fashion e- com brands in the world. And we have a 4 million strong community to prove it. How? We see no limitations, only possibilities. No failures, only learning opportunities. We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters. We’re doers. And if you dream of going to work every day to build the next big thing – then welcome home.
We are passionate about sustainability so we aim to use lower- impact materials for our products to save the environment.
We have an open position for:
Senior Data Analyst
WHO YOU ARE
Good knowledge on BigQuery, Google Analytics and Tableau and report automation in general and if you have experience with Phyton is a plus.
Experience in retail/consumer/e-commerce companies and products highly desirable
Experience working in startups and dynamic environments
Experience in Digital Analytics and Google Tag Manager
Have a go-getter attitude with a high energy level and the ability to come up with new ideas and execute rapidly
Fluent in business English, both speaking and in writing
WHAT YOU'LL DO
Create, schedule and automate reports using tools like Tableau, Google Analytics, BigQuery and Python.
Design and perform detailed analyses to help deepen understanding of customer activity across all digital platforms including web, mobile, connected devices, and video subscription services. Techniques may include statistical analyses, mathematical models (conversions, churn, and retention), experiments (A/B testing), optimization, data mining, predictive analytics, data investigation, visualisation, and reporting.
You will define data concepts and measurements with the product team and work towards optimising the customer experience on-site.
Understand digital analytics requirements, translate that into executable technical projects, implement the analytics tags, and specify required development changes to enable improved reporting and insights.
Effectively communicate quantitative findings (storytelling with data), make and defend meaningful conclusions and recommendations, and identify and interpret trends and relationships to product and business stakeholders.
Create visualisations to make data easily accessible across the organisation.
WHY YOU WILL ENJOY WORKING WITH US

start-up working environment
global environment
personal and professional development
a number of voluntary benefits
freedom to add value/make a difference

Location: The position may be Hybrid based in NA-KD's offices in Gothenburg Sweden or fully remote within Sweden.
Apply now or get in touch by sending your CV to: email: iryna.gnatyshyn@na-kd.com

Title: Data Science Lead
Description:

Data analyst, engineer, or scientist degree.
Proficiency in statistical models
Machine Learning skills are a must
Proficiency in Python, Pandas, NumPy, etc., is a must
Proficiency in Excel is a must
Tableau and/or Power BI is a plus

Excellent proficiency in English, both verbally and written

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
About MATCHi
Having spent the past decade within the world of racket sports, we know one thing that is certain: It’s growing. Like never before. Each and every day, thousands of new people decide to embark on their own racket sports journey. We’re happy to play a part in this, making the games we all know and love more accessible through user-friendly tech.
Our journey began in 2012, and our vision has been the same ever since: To be the obvious platform for the global racket sports community - for both venues and players alike. Although we’re only just getting started, we’re now widely considered to be the fastest-growing company within the industry. All this is possible through our commitment and passion for racket sports.
The numbers speak for themselves: 1400 venues connected, over 1 million players using our app, and close to 100 employees spread out across the globe.
We are looking for a Data Analyst to participate in MATCHis journey towards a more data informed culture helping us make better business decisions and build a better experience for our customers. You are a team player with a genuine interest and passion for data and details. You're both communicative, curious, precise and you share knowledge and ideas with a brave heart and a focused mind.
As a Data Analyst at MATCHi you will:
Be a key team player in a newly started, growing data team.
Work with our data stack and make sure MATCHi’s data is prepared and available for analytics and operations, both for internal and external stakeholders.
Ensure appropriate data/tools/dashboards to measure data and enable deeper analysis.
Understand strategy and KPIs and be able to align reports and insights based on them. Identify and investigate trends, anomalies and opportunities.
Handle ingestion of data into our data lake and the ETL process
Handle securely sharing of data with our customers and players
Help MATCHi take data informed decisions and be proactive in its decisions by identifying trends early through data
We prefer that you to have:
3+ years of experience working as a Data Analyst
Passion for data with extensive experience supporting development and deployment of production ready code
Understanding for hidden technical debt and live by best practices and tooling around data and cloud architectures
Knowledge of data infrastructure technologies such as Redshift, DBT, DMS, etc.
Good knowledge in SQL and Python and you aim for the highest quality in your code
Attentiveness to detail and committed to data integrity and ability to evaluate data for accuracy and errors
Good knowledge and experience in BI tools and how to present data and analytical views to different stakeholders and target groups.
AWS, multi-tenant analytics and machine learning experience is a big plus
What we offer:
A collaborative team and a culture of trust and autonomy
An opportunity to work at a rapidly scaling company
A modern office with the possibility of a flexible working setup
A possibility to work with a product that helps people live a more social and active life connected to a passion
A chance to work with data from multiple sources both on B2B and B2C sides
Huge possibilities to learn new things and lots of opportunities for personal development
Great benefits like massage, PT and padel lunches with the best colleagues ever!
If you think this opportunity sounds GREAT and you're interested in joining us, simply apply down below or at the top of this page.

Title: Data analyst
Description:
Job Description
Taking ownership of the data warehouse and its role as the source of reporting throughout the company
Ensuring data quality and consistently expanding the content of the data warehouse
Ensuring all stakeholders within the business have access to relevant reporting in clear dashboards using a variety of tools
Working closely with specialised teams across the business on data projects to build a better understanding of their department’s performance
Presenting analytical findings
Take part of product discussions and prioritisation

Qualifications
Minimum 1-2 years of experience in business intelligence, business analytics, data engineering or similar roles
Experience working in a fast-paced environment, balancing multiple responsibilities and projects
Experience acquiring data from various sources (APIs, data warehouses, scraping)
Experience dissecting complex, quantitative business problems and delivering actionable solutions
Experience communicating and presenting information to a range of stakeholders
You are fluent in English

A plus
You have experience from ride-hailing or e-scooter industry.
Additional Information
A cool 20% off your personal Vembla orders, be the first to test out new products!
A unique opportunity to be an early bird and have an impact on our strategy
A steep learning curve, the possibility to work in an energised and dynamic team within a fast-paced environment
Flat company structure where taking leadership is encouraged.

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Description:
As Senior Data Analyst you will be responsible for end-to-end coordination of Power BI reports development for assigned business areas:
– Collection and prioritization of reporting requirements from business stakeholders
– Development of new and enhancement of existing reports (Jira is used as workflow management tool).
– Internal coordination of back-end development and overall reports production process
– Where needed – additional data exploration, sourcing and modelling, development, and deployment of changes in the reporting cubes.
– Collaboration with Data Delivery team on productionizing data requirements.
You will act as the main contact person for the relevant stakeholders, high level of independently is expected
Specific areas to cover:
Handle all reporting needs in Sales & Leasing area – development of new and enhancement of existing reports; co-own Sales & Leasing reporting cube with Data Delivery team, development, and implementation of changes to leasing data model.
Other areas may be assigned based on needs and prioritization of the team.
Support ad-hoc Power BI reports development for various stakeholders based on need, both from warehouse integrated data as well as stand-alone sources.
Power BI usage reporting (follow up on usage of existing reports).
The consultant can work fully remotley, but must be relatively same time zone.
Requirements:Must have: Data modelling & DAX, SQL, Power Automate, Azure analytics, Azure DataBricks, Python, Jira, fluent in English.Extensive experience with Power BI reports & dashboards design and development full cycle, both new and re-development of existing reports.Knowledge and experience with leasing & tenant management data is highly appreciated.
Experience coaching/teaching Power BI to starter level users is highly appreciated.
Nice to have: PowerApps, BigQuery/GCP; Google Analytics/GA4.

Title: Climate Data Analyst Kalmar
Description:
Kalmar keeps global trade moving. Our innovative solutions contribute to every fourth container movement in the world and help transform the future of cargo handling. We believe in collaboration, delivering on our promises and that people make the difference.
Making your next move count

Do you want to make a real impact on the world? We are now looking for a Climate Data Analyst in Kalmar.

In this role you will collect, analyse and present information about potential business opportunities and KPI data within the field of Kalmar climate management to drive strategic and operational decisions. This role is primarily focused on assisting with collecting, analysing and reporting a variety of data to properly drive the sustainability and climate agenda and meet the commitments of being a Science Based target company. Close collaboration with the Cargotec Mission Climate team will also be required. Product use phase data analytics will also be required from time to time.

This position is based in Ljungby and you will report to Kalmar’s Head of Sustainability. This is a hybrid job with the possibility to work from home.
Main tasks and responsibilities

Your main tasks will consist of assessing data requirements and supply master data related to Life Cycle Assessment (LCA), carbon intensity (tCO2e/M€) of portfolio, Greenhouse Gas Protocol (GHG), Supply chain engagement and performance, Science Based Targets Initiative (SBTi), CRU International data related to steel. You will identify opportunities for improvements with data availability, enterprise data architecture, data processing, reporting, and analytics and audit data quality and identify gaps. You will also deliver results to various stakeholders in a self-service reporting environment and by delivering reports and comparative analytics as needed and coordinate information flow of the above-mentioned topics within the corporation (assure that respective businesses are aware of the inputs).

Other tasks:

Create climate data models and system reports, scenario analysis, etc.
Act as an advocate for data and reporting needs for Sustainability
Support Kalmar and Cargotec to build & maintain CO2 emission reporting systems, integrated with sourcing data and adding CO2 emissions impact in sourcing projects. This includes supporting IM to harmonise and change system platforms to control master data
Build & maintain Eco portfolio reporting systems and emissions tools.

What you’ll need to succeed

Typically university (Bachelor's degree) level or vocational qualification / relevant working experience
Familiar with Kalmar or Cargotec master data and key systems (e.g. GCP, SAP, ERP ́s, CR360)
Preferred experience with management of large amounts and complexity of data, reporting, or analytics
Undertake advanced statistical analysis and use statistical tools and models
Emissions calculation (GHG Protocol) and Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) knowledge or willingness to learn
Solid understanding of best practices of reporting and data visualisation practices.


Our new colleague is someone with strong communication skills, fluent in English, a data-oriented problem solver, able to work independently to complete given assignments.
You have a background in Information Management and a preferred experience with data quality and auditing, project management experience is beneficial.
You will be part of

We believe in our people as it is our people who really make the difference. We always work in close collaboration with our customers, deliver on our promises and never walk away no matter how big the challenge. We succeed because we do it together.

With us, you will have the opportunity to realise your potential and become an important member of our global team.
Interested to join?

For further information please contact Mette Kjems Baerentzen, Head of Sustainability, by email at mette.kjems.baerentzen@kalmarglobal.com

If you are excited about this opportunity, please submit your application by 24.02.2023.
Kalmar is part of Cargotec
Kalmar offers the widest range of cargo handling solutions and services to ports, terminals, distribution centres and to the heavy industry. Kalmar is the industry forerunner in terminal automation and in energy efficient container handling, with one in four container movements around the globe being handled by a Kalmar solution. Through its extensive product portfolio, global service network and ability to enable a seamless integration of different terminal processes, Kalmar improves the efficiency of every move. www.kalmarglobal.com

Kalmar is part of Cargotec. Cargotec's (Nasdaq Helsinki: CGCBV) sales in 2021 totalled approximately EUR 3.3 billion and it employs around 11,500 people.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Ingrid is hiring! Our Data & Analytics team is growing team is growing—are you our new Data Analyst?
Ingrid is on a mission to solve the largest problem with global e-commerce and create the world’s best delivery experiences.
Ingrid provides consumers with a much better shopping experience through intelligent choice of delivery options and flexible last mile deliveries—on their own terms. Our key objective is to increase merchant credibility and consumer convenience. We have successfully done so since 2015. By integrating Ingrid’s SaaS-platform, e-commerce merchants are able to improve online shopping experiences for all consumers and any purchase.
We’re the best at what we do and always looking to hire the best people around.

About the role
As a data analyst you will be part of Ingrid’s Data & Analytics team which is responsible for enabling Ingrid teams and customers with data insights. Your primary focus will be to support the product team and help them to understand how our products are performing and how they can be further improved by using data insights. This role requires that you’re curious to know how a product works behind the scenes but also what’s making the customer enjoy the product. We believe that you love working with huge amounts of data in a complex environment where you see the opportunity to further improve your skills within the data & analytics space.

Examples of responsibilities within this role:
Build a strong understanding of Ingrid products and the data underlying them.
Proactively analyze performance of Ingrid’s products and help drive product development using data.
Maintain and develop new metrics related to Ingrid products
Refine existing curated data layers as well as developing new ones.
Contribute to the data & analytics team overall structure.

About you
You have 1-2 years of experience in the data & analytics space
You have completed a degree in statistics, mathematics, economics, computer science or an equivalent education or possess relevant practical experience
You have solid experience with SQL (BigQuery or similar is a plus)
You have experience in visualizing and communicating insights from data (Metabase or similar is a plus)
You have very good communication skills in English, both written and oral

Meritorious
Previous experience working with product analytics
Experience with statistical programming tools such as Python or R.
A/B testing experience (designing experiments and analyzing results).
Experience working with Git and analytics engineering tools such as DBT.

What we offer:
Flexible cooperation and a unique, informal atmosphere
The opportunity to develop your skills and gain experience by working with strong international brands on innovative projects
Support from experienced team members
Experiencing great teamwork at a highly ambitious startup

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Hej, Truecaller is calling you from Stockholm, Sweden! Ready to pick up?
Truecaller transformed how we communicate when we launched in 2009 in Stockholm, Sweden.
Our mission is to build trust everywhere by making tomorrow’s communication smarter, safer and more efficient. We focus on bringing smart services with big social impacts, like protecting people from fraud, harassment, and scam calls or messages. We identify new numbers from anywhere in the world and build a space for trustworthy conversations, for those that matter. Truecaller is loved by over 330 million people around the world and is growing very rapidly across regions.
Who we are:
The world’s #1 caller ID and spam blocking service for Android and iOS.
A team of +350 people from ~35 different nationalities, spread across our headquarters in Stockholm and offices in Bangalore, Mumbai, Gurgaon, Tel Aviv and Nairobi.
Backed by some of the most prominent investors in the world such as Sequoia Capital and Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers.
We, the User Monetization team create and hold an organizational-wide mindset and culture that everyone can and should contribute to monetization. Our goal is to ensure that our current profitable and rapidly growing subscriptions business runs flawlessly while empowering the org to execute on future product road maps.
As a Data Analyst in the User Monetization team you will get the opportunity to work with 350M active users in a freemium environment, you will be strongly focused on collecting, organizing, analyzing and interpreting Truecaller data. You will draw insightful conclusions from your analysis with the aim of enhancing the product roadmap, business plan and customer experience.
You will be Focusing on Revenue and Subscriptions and will track on a daily basis the KPIs and trends from multiple current data sources. Building and maintaining Data Studio and Looker Dashboards, you will provide daily updates to the team or deep dive reports. You will have a core responsibility in providing the right info to the team to be able to take the right decision for daily business.
What do we expect from you
1 to 2 years of experience doing quantitative analysis (experience working for a Product oriented company is a plus)
Expertise in data visualization tools, such as Google Data Studio, Looker, QlikSens,Tableau, PowerBI, etc.
Experience using SQL to extract, transform and analyze data
Ability to communicate results of analyses in a clear and effective manner
Good applied statistics skills, such as distributions, statistical testing, regression, etc.
Ability to initiate and drive projects to completion with minimal guidance
Good communication skills.

What will you work on
Identify different sources and type of information from the different app stores, internal analytics, Campaign management tools, AB test solutions…
Collect, clean, organize, analyze and interpret application data and usage, draw insightful conclusions to enable data-driven product enhancements
Create visual interpretations of data on Data Studio or Looker, produce graphs and charts with insightful notes and summaries
Analyze customer data and assist product development in finding new innovative ways to optimize conversion and retention
Support the management in identifying, measuring and following up on key metrics
Analyze campaigns and user journey results in order to improve conversion and retention tactics
Provide regular, accurate and comprehensive statistical reports
Provide objective insight and analysis to influence decision making
Keep up to date knowledge on external market and data research to compare our metrics and create a value-added analysis
It would be great if you also have
Experience in revenue and subscription key metrics is a plus
Worked with Campaign management tools and metrics
Good understanding of A/B experiments and hands-on experience is a plus.
Good scripting and programming skills
Experience with Python and R programming language

Sounds like your dream job?
We will fill the position as soon as we find the right candidate, so please send your application as soon as possible. As part of the recruitment process, we will conduct a background check.
This position is based in Stockholm, Sweden.
We only accept applications in English.
What we offer:

A smart, talented and agile team: An international team where ~35 nationalities are working together in several locations and time zones with a learning, sharing and fun environment.
A great compensation package: Competitive salary, 30 days of paid vacation, flexible working hours, private health insurance and pension contribution, Udemy membership to keep learning and improving, gym membership.
Great tech tools: Pick the computer and phone that you fancy the most within our budget ranges.
A new life in Sweden: We offer full visa sponsorship and relocation assistance when required. Of course, we support your beloved ones as well!
Do it your way: For the days you're working from home, we provide you with an attractive budget for creating your cozy office at home.
Office life: Enjoy your days with a wide range of yummy snacks and beverages, and have fun at our playroom! As well, exciting company parties and team activities such as Lab days, Running team, Geek lunch!

Come as you are:
Truecaller is diverse, equal and inclusive. We need a wide variety of backgrounds, perspectives, beliefs and experiences in order to keep building our great products. No matter where you are based, which language you speak, your accent, race, religion, color, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, etc. All those things make you who you are, and that’s why we would love to meet you.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Do you want to be a part of a new Analytics Operations team and get to work in an inspiring environment? Then you should keep reading!
DevPort are now looking for a Data Analyst to join our clients new Analytics Operations team. The Analytics Operations team should act as a catalyst and take responsibility for analytics value creation in all phases; from early ideation with stakeholders to creating runtime dashboards and data pipelines or guiding superusers to help them create their own dashboards. We also cooperate with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to run AI/ML models in operations. The Analytics Operations team is new and as such you will be part of developing the unit and creating successful use cases.
Our clients new Data, Analytics & AI organization is focused on unleashing the value of data collected from connected customer assets. The team are set out to drive the transformation into a data driven culture, where Data, Analytics & AI/ML are an integral part in their services and internal processes. By spanning across Data Foundation, Data Analytics and Data Science they can provide their stakeholders with actionable insights and take ownership of the whole process from ideation and exploration to analytics operations.

About the role
Drive the data journey by connecting with stakeholders, running workshops, identify opportunities and take it from idea to value.
Develop state-of-the art solutions, dashboards, and insight reports.
Stay at the forefront in the analytics space and share knowledge and experience with colleagues.

Your profile
You have a degree in a relevant field or practical experience from utilizing data to drive change.
You are a creative, entrepreneurial problem-solver with an inquisitive attitude and are not afraid of complex challenges or unconventional approaches.
You routinely use dashboarding as a tool for problem solving, and are experienced in at least one dashboarding solution (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, QuickSight, Grafana).
You confidently and systematically build analysis approaches from scratch, including data extraction, scripting and/or programming in relevant languages and analysis with creation of informative and appealing visualizations.
You are a communicative person that builds and maintains trust with stakeholders and colleagues.
Humorous; because, in the end, working in the team should be fun.

What can we offer you?
You will be part of a highly skilled analytics team that together with our stakeholders creates great value in short- and long-term engagements. In this team you will be able to make a data-driven impact on sustainable transport solutions for our client, their customers and society at large - and have fun while doing it. Your workplace will be based in Lindholmen in Gothenburg.

Application
Apply by following the steps below. If you have any questions regarding the position, send an email to Elin Thulin at elin.thulin@devport.se
I am looking forward to read you application!

About DevPort
DevPort is a technology consulting company in an expansive development phase with headquarter in Gothenburg and offices in Stockholm, Linköping, Helsingborg and Karlskrona. DevPort has its core competence in the automotive industry and employs more than 500 people in three business areas - Digital solutions, production development and product development.
We are proud of our employees and of collaborating with several of the world's leading vehicle manufacturers, companies in the defense industry and other development-intensive industries.
We are characterized by a family culture with entrepreneurship, competence, security and a community that infuses the company's operations and contributes to a pleasant and inspiring workplace.

Title: Qlik Sense developer and Data Analyst
Description:
Job brief
We are looking for a passionate Data Analyst. The successful candidate will turn data into information, information into insight and insight into business decisions.

Job Duties
The Data analyst will be developing and maintaining Qlik Sense applications based on requirements of the business, building and managing data source libraries, and help develop the usage within the organisation. They will also monitor performance and quality control plans to identify improvements.

Responsibilities
Interpret data, analyze results using statistical techniques and provide ongoing reports
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets
Design and maintain data model structure
Develop and implement BI applications for reporting and data analytics that optimize efficiency and quality
Acquire, and manage, data from primary or secondary data sources
Train end-users on new reports and dashboards
Provide quality assurance of imported data
Work with management to prioritize business and information needs
Locate and define new process improvement opportunities

Requirements
Proven working experience as a Data Analyst or Business Data Analyst
+3 years experience of QlikView or Qlik Sense
Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques
Strong knowledge of and experience with reporting packages (Business Objects etc), databases (SQL etc), programming (XML, Javascript, or ETL frameworks)
Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing datasets (Excel, SPSS, SAS etc)
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy
Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings
BS in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Information Management or Statistics
Ability to work with stakeholders to assess potential risks
Ability to translate business requirements into non-technical, lay terms
High level written and verbal communication skills
We also want you to live our core values:
innovate
be curious
have fun
work smart
take responsibility
#LI-TB1

Title: Data analyst
Description:
Ansök nu
Data Analyst
At Coop we are boldly going where no one has gone before, creating new standards within the industry as a whole. We are not exactly sure what the future of the Swedish food industry will look like, but we know that data, and your analytical capabilities will be shaping it.
Team AI and Business Intelligence are looking for a Data Analyst to join our growing Analytics branch. You will bring your analytical skills to the table to develop data and insights solutions that help our needs in saving time and money, improving health and providing sustainable food.
Sounds interesting - wait until you hear what you actually will work with:
Dive into massive amounts of data residing on a state of the art platform.
Coach Coop to work harder, better, faster, stronger with data to change our business for the better
Lead through examples by providing clear, actionable insights through dashboards and analytical deep dives
While doing this, you will also belong to an awesome team of data people (analysts, scientists and engineers)

Kvalifikationer
Skills we value
While great resumes are great, we also believe that you can come a long way with the right analytical mindset and can-do attitude! Hopefully, you possess one or many of these skills/experiences:
Swedish speaking, business acumen and willingness to understand modern retail challenge
Expertise in pushing insights through modern BI tools (Power BI, Tableau, Qlik)
Self sufficient (i.e. how to navigate stack overflow) when it comes to easier programming tasks with python, acquiring data from relational databases (SQL) and how to work in a cloud environment (Azure, GCP or AWS)
Familiar with statistics or machine learning concepts to know when there’s a time and place for that
Degree in Economics, Statistics Computer Science, Engineering or numerate subject
What does Coop offer?
A place for personal growth - you will work with several degrees of freedom and with that comes great responsibilities
A place to practice and develop your hard skills - whether it’s the latest cloud technologies or stakeholder management
A palace for fun - a prestige less environment where we will focus on what actually matters - great environmentally friendly food for everyone!
Coop HQ is located in Solna Business Park, about 10 minutes from the city centre. It is a spacious office with a green slide leading you down to the company restaurant - because great environmentally friendly food is what it’s all about in the end. Contact person Jakob Liljedahl

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
What is this about?
Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions. We understand how Computer Vision and AI can benefit the society. We stand ready to use our expertise to facilitate businesses in their journey into the era of AI. We work with several clients with various industry fields in close collaboration with top universities in Sweden.

Synteda is actively working on several unique products and solutions in various fields. Dream-innovate-create is our work process were our ideas go through different stages. We create successful solutions by checking feasibility of our product idea (POC) and develop our solution working with agile methodologies until we reach a complete full-scale product.

Synteda has a core team of highly qualified experts that provide assessment to identify challenges and explore different ideas to enhance effectiveness and develop specific algorithms to overcome company challenges. Synteda is built on ethical awareness, curiosity, transparency, respect, participation and last but not least science.

Synteda is growing rapidly and we are looking for a talented data analyst to join our team of experts. You are an analytical thinker and detail-oriented who enjoy data mining and continuously want to find a better solution.
What are we looking for?
Responsibilities
Work on our various platforms and customer assignments.
Data collection process using specialized analytic tools to analyze opportunities, issues and areas of improvement
Perform analyses of custom datasets.
Generate ideas and build tools to improve data collection quality and processes.
Utilize statistical techniques such as regression analysis to develop and improve models.
Support and enhance data to facilitate successful implementation of procedures.
Create reports and presentations to direct business strategy.
Visualize, analyze and report data anomalies.
Brainstorm, plan and prioritize different functions.

Skills
Experience in statistical modeling and data mining techniques.
Understandable knowledge in Python and/or R.
Understandable knowledge within ETL.
Excellent database skills with previous experienced extracting, manipulating and querying large datasets.
Good knowledge of cloud such as Google Cloud, AWS and Azure for deployment and management of developed models.
Experience with data visualization tools such as Power BI, Tableau, Microsoft Access, SPSS modeler, SAS analytics or similar.
Experience working with visual analysis like Google Analytics, Data Studio.
Knowledge of AI and machine learning models.
Previous experience building machine learning models and data visualization.
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.
Experience of agile development methodologies.
Good communication and presentation skills.
Languages: Swedish and English.

Title: Data Analyst, Customer Meeting Points, Customer Domain, Group Digital, Ingka Group
Description:
Who you are

At IKEA, you’re welcome no matter where you come from, what you believe, and what you look like. We don’t even care how you have furnished your home. We’re interested in you simply because you’re you. Our different views, backgrounds, and personalities make us better understand our customers, give us more fun at work and spark more and better ideas. Perhaps your unique take on something could lead to a great idea that creates a better everyday life for the many people.

As a (Senior) Data Analyst, you are an important part in guiding the organisation on how to make best use of one of the world’s possibly largest and most extensive data sets for Web and App. With a growth mindset, you take ownership, enjoy collaborating with various stakeholders, including product owners and engineers, and building a network in a large organisation. You focus on the customer and what the insight from the data means for them.

You also recognize yourself in some of the following:

You’ve experience as a Business Analyst, Data/Web/App Analyst or Data Scientist
You’ve extensive knowledge of data pre-processing techniques, e.g. how to handle missing data
You’ve got a solid knowledge of SQL and the role it plays in data analysis
You’re familiar with cloud computing environments, e.g. Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
You’ve broad knowledge of relevant scripting languages (such as Python) and the role of notebook environments for sharing findings and code with others
You’ve got a good understanding of collaborative software engineering practices (Agile, DevOps, GitOps), in which solutions evolve through the effort of self-organising cross-functional teams
You’re familiar with digital product development principles and the importance of rapid validated learning cycles to optimise performance long-term (preferably in a retail setting)
You do love storytelling and use visualisations of data to explain facts
You’re excited about IKEA’s values and vision of creating a better everyday life for the many people!

The IKEA culture and values are very much a part of our business and day-to-day work life. For you to thrive and grow with IKEA it’s important for us that you share our values! You can read more regarding our values and life at IKEA on our website www.ikea.com.

We are looking for both a Senior Data Analyst and a Data Analyst.

What you'll be doing day to day

Within the Customer Domain of Data & Analytics, you’ll be a part of the Customer Meeting Points area team that focus on Online Data and Tracking pillar both for Web (IKEA online store) and IKEA App. In collaborations mostly with Product and Engineering, you will gather both qualitative and quantitative insights that are needed to impact the roadmap of the products.

This means:
Conduct advanced data exploration and analysis to provide insights that help co-workers and stakeholders make better decisions
Evaluate the potential and usability of raw, unstructured internal and external data sources for use in product analytics and data-driven decision-making in general
Ensure that solutions fulfill and adapt to actual business needs to continuously generate value for Ingka by listening to and guiding fellow team members and co-workers from different functions

Our team within Ikea

We are proud of our vision to create a better everyday life for the many people. We’re working in different locations worldwide to facilitate our digital growth ambition. The office for this role will be Malmö, Sweden, but we act as one global team and work together on global solutions.

We want you to join our diverse team within Data & Analytics consisting of Data Engineers, Data Analysts, Data Scientists, and Data Stewards based across Sweden, the Netherlands and Spain. Our team is filled with people who enjoy good stories and welcome new team members warmly!

We see so many opportunities for what we can accomplish and have the ambition to be a world-class team. At the same time, we believe that our work is not just about solving business problems, but also about learning and having fun together!

WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU

Opportunities to have a global impact with your work on our e-commerce performance on Web & App
Flexible and modern tools: we deploy on GCP and we use lots of open-source tools
Hardware and Operating System of your choice
A team of great colleagues to learn with and from (with world-class experience)
Continuous learning (we aim to spend 20% of our working time on learning)
Flexible and friendly working environment in a truly value-based company!

Questions and support? Let's connect!

Does this sound like your next challenge? IKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global workplace. And as the world’s leader at life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us.

If you have questions regarding the recruitment process, please reach out to Annette Björkquist-Åhstedt at annette.bjorkquist-ahstedt@ingka.ikea.com

Please apply with your application in English. Note that we can’t process any applications through email. Thank you!

Studies show that members of underrepresented communities don’t apply for jobs unless they’re 100% “qualified”. If this is part of the reason you hesitate to apply, we like you to reconsider and give it a chance. Maybe your profile fits our needs much better than you think. We look forward to receiving your application.

From: “Why Women Don’t Apply for Jobs Unless They’re 100% Qualified” by Tara Sophia Mohr, August 2014”

Title: Data Science Lead
Description:
JOIN THE KODIAK HUB SLEUTH AS WE AID GLOBAL COMPANIES TO CREATE SMARTER & MORE SUSTAINABLE SUPPLY CHAINS AT SCALE.
Ready to work with something that creates real impact? Check out our opening

Who we are?

Kodiak Hub is a growth venture offering SaaS solutions engineered to revolutionize Supplier Relationship Management (SRM). We are building the next generation of B2B SaaS, based on business intelligence, automation, big data analytics, and machine learning technology, creating a blueprint of how companies optimize their interaction and collaboration with suppliers.

Our team is international and tight-knit, composed of competent and creative individuals. We double our revenue on a yearly basis, and we have an aggressive yet realistic growth model for the following years. As our product is completely novel, we are constantly figuring out innovative solutions to the market's challenges.

Join us and help us change the way companies operate in their global supply chains!

We have an opening for a Data Science Lead!

We are looking for an energetic, engaged Data Science Lead who aspires to improve the world!

As our Data Science Lead, you will be responsible for analyzing the current data from the platform, visualizing and explaining data insights to drive decision-making, both internally and externally, executing AI, machine learning, and data analysis projects, advising about the data architecture and training internal and external stakeholders.

Candidates' Requirements Attributes:
Data analyst, engineer, or scientist degree.
Proficiency in statistical models
Machine Learning skills are a must
Proficiency in Python, Pandas, NumPy, etc., is a must
Proficiency in Excel is a must
Tableau and/or Power BI is a plus
R is a plus
Excellent proficiency in English, both verbally and written

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Vi startade Signific för att kunna lösa världens mest spännande och utmanande problem. Det gör vi genom att hjälpa organisationer och team att samla in, strukturera upp och agera på insikter från stora mängder kvantitativ data. På så sätt lär de sig snabbare om hur nytta, förändring och effekt skapas.

Signific jobbar med datadrivna, vassa och nyfikna kunder som t.ex. Detectify, Transfer Galaxy, M och SVT.
Som Data Analyst-konsult på Signific hjälper du våra uppdragsgivare att ta sin data till nya, insiktsskapande nivåer. Din förståelse för både affärs- och datamodeller kombinerat med analys, verktyg och kod är superviktig för ett datadrivet, lärande arbetssätt. På Signific får du använda dina skills på stora, inspirerande problem.
Utöver att göra skillnad i dina uppdrag är du en stor del av ett framåtlutat bolag som sätter våra anställda i fokus. Vi är ett litet, flexibelt bolag med stora ambitioner och vill ha med dig på resan dit.
Vad du kommer få göra
Vi tror på en öppen approach till lösningar på våra kunders utmaningar. Vi väljer lösning efter problem och inte vice versa. Din roll kan därför variera beroende på ditt intresse och kundernas problem.
Som Data Analyst hos oss ser vi dig troligen göra några av följande saker:
Först och främst hjälpa företag skapa mer nytta av sin data
Ta fram KPI:er och mätpunkter för användarbeteende kopplat till produkter och verksamheter
Ta komplex data till modeller och analyser som löser viktiga verksamhets- och samhällsproblem
Analysera stora mängder användardata för att driva produkt- och designbeslut
Kommunicera insikter och rekommendationer
Ha en nyckelroll att förflytta team och organisationer mot ett datadrivet arbetssätt.
Få ta del av och bidra till kunskapsdelning och nyskapande kultur ihop med dina kollegor
Utvecklas åt det håll du vill
Vem vi tror du är
Vi tror på att bygga ett bolag av olika personer som på olika sätt bidrar till att vi alla trivs och lyckas. För att du ska trivas hos oss och i din roll tror vi dock att det finns några saker som du checkar av merparten av:
Som person
Ser positivt på utmaningar
Gillar att vara självgående men också att samarbeta
Nyfiken på nya teknologier och problem
Vill vara så bra som möjligt på det du gör
Gillar att sälja, kunskapsdela och/eller bidra till kulturen bland dina kollegor
I din roll
Är genuint intresserad av att lösa kunders verksamhetsproblem
Har minst fyra års arbetslivserfarenhet inom rollen eller liknande roller
Förstår vilka mått och mätetal som är viktiga för digitala produkter
Riktigt vass på att ta fram analyser av digitala produkter och tjänster i verktyg som t.ex. Google Analytics, Adobe Analytics, Mixpanel eller Amplitude
Känner dig bekväm med att göra kontextspecifika analyser när vanliga analysverktyg inte räcker till i t.ex. Excel/Google Sheets eller med programmeringsspråk som SQL, Python eller R.
Har flera års erfarenhet av att sätta upp dashboards i visualiseringsverktyg (som t.ex. Tableau, Google Analytics, Google Data Studio)
Gillar och förstår statistik (som t.ex. A/B-tester, signfikanstester och regressionsmodellering)
Noggrann men också lösningsorienterad
Trivs att jobba i agila team och kanske också i en mer ledande roll.
Har stort intresse för Data Engineering/Science/Analytics i allmänhet
Högskoleutbildning är inget krav, men konkret arbetslivserfarenhet är det.
En spännande resa där du får vara med och påverka
Vi är ett nystartat litet bolag, med ambitioner att göra stort avtryck i våra uppdrag och på längre sikt. Vi vill skapa en samling av dom bästa inom vår nisch och bygga en stark kultur av gemenskap, ambition och kunskap. Något som gör en signifikant skillnad helt enkelt.
Hos oss får du
Utmanande uppdrag inom områden du är intresserad av
Kollegor som ser möjligheter och värdet med din kunskap inom data
Vassa kollegor som gillar att lära och läras av varandra
Konkurrenskraftiga förmåner
Inkluderande och hållbar arbetsmiljö
Vill du vara med och göra skillnad?

Title: Data Analyst Internship for Validation
Description:
Our Validation department in Västerås is looking for the next generation of passionate and autonomous data analysts who want to join our mission to develop the next level of green batteries for our customers.
This is your chance to start your career in the Li-ion technology industry. The Validation team is working directly with customer projects and cell development to ensure the excellent performance & safety of Northvolt’s products – batteries. Increasing amount of test demands especially in performance and life testing generate huge amounts of data, which needs to be processed, visualized, and summarized.
During the internship, you will be part of an agile data team that works towards standardizing, automatizing and improving data analysis methods for our validation team. You will develop data analysis tools (in python) for validation, support with data visualization and generate automated data summaries. On top you will have the chance to learn about Li-ion batteries and get to know all phases of the testing process, starting from setting test procedures up to the results presentation.
Key responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Develop data analysis standards and tools for automated analysis
Create visualizations and reports validating the performance of our Li-ion cells
Help the team to perform and innovate
Gain insight into data analysis, software development and Li-ion batteries
In joining us, you will get the chance to have a real impact on our success story in Sweden (to start with) and see the results of your work.
The person we are looking for is passionate about developing knowledge in data analysis and has a curious mindset. Ideally, you are eager to learn, take ownership of the tasks on hand and like to work and communicate with colleagues from various backgrounds and cultures.
Apply with CV in English or your complete LinkedIn profile.
Up to 6 months of internship is preferred but can be discussed - please state the time period possible for you.
Monthly compensation. Planned starting date is as soon as possible.
Skills & Requirements
We believe that you have:
Excellent English written and oral communication skills.
Python skills: Data analysis and visualization (jupyter, pandas, matplotlib/seaborn/bokeh/plotly, etc.)
Comfortable using version control tools (e.g. git)
Quick learner and capable of independently driving tasks to the end
Curious and capable of working in fast paced environments with a proactive attitude
Passionate and purpose driven
Bonus points for:
Engineering foundation with understanding in electrical, mechanical, and chemical domains
Familiarity with data storage technologies (SQL DB, GCS/S3)
Familiarity with Automotive Development Processes
Knowledge of battery industry is an advantage
Experience in multicultural, start-up environment
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment
Fast paced & entrepreneurial culture
Warrant program
Wellness grant

Title: Data/Risk Analyst to SEB Kort
Description:
Categories
Risk, SEB Kort
19 February 2023
Location
Solna
SEB Kort Bank AB is a fully owned subsidiary of the SEB Group with approximately 600 employees operating in Finland, Sweden, Denmark and Norway. SEB Kort’s business targets two strategic areas; corporates and consumers. In both areas, SEB Kort works from two different brand perspectives; our own brands, which are Eurocard and SEB brand, and several partner brands. The CRO function is a Nordic function, reporting to the CEO of SEB Kort.

What you will be doing
You will report to the Chief Risk Officer and be a part of a dynamic and analytical team, with responsibility for the risk governance of SEB Kort. You will develop your knowledge of SEB Kort’s risk profile, while working with analysis and reporting of all risk types. Forums for reporting include SEB Kort’s management team and BoD, as well as Swedish FSA and EBA.

You will be supporting the business, and other teams, with data driven insights and recommendations to stakeholders. This includes developing the monitoring process of financial risk and ensuring the processes of controlling, identifying gaps and following up on mitigating activities.

You will develop the risk policies, along with defining and controlling tolerance levels. You will be involved in the risk assessment process, as well as NPAC.

You will be collaborating with programmers, engineers, and domain leads to identify opportunities for process improvements, recommend system modifications, and support in developing policies for data governance. The business development at SEB Kort is carried out in an agile organization (SAFe framework) where you will play a part as stakeholder and business expert.

Who we are looking for
Relevant experience working as a data analyst preferably with risk management
Preferable experience from second line of defence in a financial institution, IRB models, ECL, Definition of Default, regulatory reports such as SREP, interaction with FSA, etc.
Programming skills in SAS, SQL or similar
Experience using statistical tools to interpret data sets to identify trends and patterns
Experience working with databases and data visualization using Tableau or Qlik is meriting
Experience within Non-Financial Risk is meriting
Fluency in English is a requirement, Swedish is meriting
Master’s Degree in statistics, mathematics, computer science, engineering, economics or another quantitative discipline

As a person, you are a highly motivated, independent, proactive, structured and delivery-focused with a strategic mind-set. You are a team player with a high degree of integrity and an ability to work cross-functions with different units while managing stakeholders’ requirements and agenda.

What we offer
It is our fundamental belief that inclusion and diversity is crucial for our future success. We strive to have an inclusive, value-driven culture where employees feel valued, respected and involved irrespective of who they are, what they believe or where they come from.

Ready to join?
You are welcome with your application as soon as you can, but no later than 2023-02-19. We select candidates ongoing. If you have any questions, contact Sebastian Vesterlund, Talent Acquisition Partner sebastian.vesterlund@seb.se

At SEB, we have always believed that the future depends on turning great ideas into reality. Ever since we welcomed our first customer in 1856, we have been a catalyst for positive change by providing responsible advice and capital to people with ideas for the future. Grounded in our long history and strong heritage, we want to create long-term value for all our stakeholders by being curious about what the future holds. We have a strong ambition to accelerate the pace towards a sustainable future for people, businesses, and society. Our skilled and dedicated employees stand by our customers in good times and bad and offer financial products and services that meet their ever-changing needs – both in our home markets in northern Europe and through our international network around the world.
Read more: https://sebgroup.com/

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
TV4 söker en affärdriven data analyst som vill utvecklas i ett nyfiket, samarbetsinriktat och användarfokuserat team
Här får du möjligheten att vara en del av ett nyfiket analysteam på TV4, Sveriges ledande kommersiella mediehus med en av Sveriges största streamingtjänster, TV4 Play.
Är det här din nästa möjlighet?
TV-landskapet har förändrats och fortsätter att förändras. Användare får fler tjänster att välja mellan och ställer högre krav. Det innebär att vi ständigt utmanas i att utveckla vårt erbjudande för att möta användarnas behov. För att optimera både innehåll och tjänst jobbar vi som organisation mot att bli mer och mer datadrivna.
Det ställer krav på oss analytiker att förstå hur användarna konsumerar vårt innehåll på alla plattformar. Vi är ett team på 8 personer med olika analysroller som tillsammans stöttar organisationen med användaranalys, undersökningar, rapportering, prediktiv analys och digital analys. Som data analyst är din främsta uppgift att samla och analysera data från vår dataplattform och presentera för olika stakeholders i organisationen. Det kan handla om att öka förståelsen för användarbasen och dess konsumtion av innehåll till att besvara konkreta frågeställningar och ta fram underlag till specifika beslut. Du kommer jobba nära flera olika avdelningar och det är viktigt att du är intresserad av att förstå affären och gillar att kommunicera analyser och insikter.
En av våra styrkor som team är att vi kan dra nytta av varandras analyskompetens i större analysprojekt såsom kvantitativa och kvalitativa data. Vi tror på att kombinera olika datakällor och metoder för att leverera bästa tänkbara insikter till verksamheten. Dessutom gör det jobbet roligare!
Hos oss får du jobba med stora datamängder, TV4 Play har över en miljon inloggade användare per vecka. Vi har ett nära samarbete med vårt datateam som ansvarar för att tillgängliggöra data i GCP.
Det finns goda möjligheter att själv påverka rollens utformning, huvuduppgifterna som rollen omfattar är:
Analysera användarbeteende
Användarsegmentering
Innehålls- och tittarprediktioner
Sätta upp dashboards
Ad-hoc analyser
Är det här du?
För att lyckas i rollen som Data Analyst tror vi att:
Du har minst 3 års erfarenhet av att arbeta som Data Analyst med stora datamängder
Du har relevant utbildning inom statistik, matematik, programmering eller motsvarande
Du har goda kunskaper inom SQL och Python och/eller R
Om du har erfarenhet av att jobba i Google cloud platform och DBT är det meriterande
Du är van att visualisera och presentera data i Tableau, Looker, Power Point eller liknande
Du har god förståelse och intresse för användarbeteende och affärslogik för en streamingtjänst
Mer än bara ett jobb!
Oavsett vilket jobb du söker hos oss, ger vi dig verktygen och stödet du behöver för att styra din personliga utveckling. Vi vill hjälpa dig att utvecklas både på ett personligt plan och i din yrkesroll. Hos oss blir du en del av ett kreativt, motiverande och välkomnande företag där alla kan vara sig själva, med likvärdiga möjligheter att utvecklas. Förutom en attraktiv och inkluderande arbetsmiljö erbjuder vi ett brett utbud av olika förmåner.
Intresserad?
Tveka inte att skicka in din ansökan om du vill bli en del av vårt team! Om du vill veta mer om jobbet är du välkommen att kontakta mig på asa.wallin@tv4.se eller 073-785 40 17.
Tjänsten tillhör Unionens avtalsområde och fackliga frågor ställs till unionen@tv4.se
Vi ser fram emot din ansökan. För att kunna hantera dina personuppgifter på ett säkert sätt, ber vi dig att ansöka via vårt rekryteringssystem. Vi har inte möjlighet att ta emot ansökningar via e-post eller andra kanaler. Urval och intervjuer sker löpande, tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas innan sista ansökningsdatum.
Om oss
Vi är Nordens största kommersiella tv-bolag. Vi är ledande i utvecklingen av rörlig bild och digitaliseringen av tv-industrin med hjälp av kraften och styrkan i våra varumärken – och hos våra fantastiska medarbetare. Med en stor mängd tv-kanaler och andra tjänster, bjuder vi in hela Sverige till en tv-upplevelse i världsklass. Att ständigt vara relevanta, stå på användarnas sida och att vara en del av Sverige – det är några av våra viktigaste uppgifter.
Välkommen till TV4 - en del av Telia – Home to your next big opportunity!
