Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Do you want to be a part of a new Analytics Operations team and get to work in an inspiring environment? Then you should keep reading!
DevPort are now looking for a Data Analyst to join our clients new Analytics Operations team. The Analytics Operations team should act as a catalyst and take responsibility for analytics value creation in all phases; from early ideation with stakeholders to creating runtime dashboards and data pipelines or guiding superusers to help them create their own dashboards. We also cooperate with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to run AI/ML models in operations. The Analytics Operations team is new and as such you will be part of developing the unit and creating successful use cases.
Our clients new Data, Analytics & AI organization is focused on unleashing the value of data collected from connected customer assets. The team are set out to drive the transformation into a data driven culture, where Data, Analytics & AI/ML are an integral part in their services and internal processes. By spanning across Data Foundation, Data Analytics and Data Science they can provide their stakeholders with actionable insights and take ownership of the whole process from ideation and exploration to analytics operations.

About the role
Drive the data journey by connecting with stakeholders, running workshops, identify opportunities and take it from idea to value.
Develop state-of-the art solutions, dashboards, and insight reports.
Stay at the forefront in the analytics space and share knowledge and experience with colleagues.

Your profile
You have a degree in a relevant field or practical experience from utilizing data to drive change.
You are a creative, entrepreneurial problem-solver with an inquisitive attitude and are not afraid of complex challenges or unconventional approaches.
You routinely use dashboarding as a tool for problem solving, and are experienced in at least one dashboarding solution (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, QuickSight, Grafana).
You confidently and systematically build analysis approaches from scratch, including data extraction, scripting and/or programming in relevant languages and analysis with creation of informative and appealing visualizations.
You are a communicative person that builds and maintains trust with stakeholders and colleagues.
Humorous; because, in the end, working in the team should be fun.

What can we offer you?
You will be part of a highly skilled analytics team that together with our stakeholders creates great value in short- and long-term engagements. In this team you will be able to make a data-driven impact on sustainable transport solutions for our client, their customers and society at large - and have fun while doing it. Your workplace will be based in Lindholmen in Gothenburg.

Application
Apply by following the steps below. If you have any questions regarding the position, send an email to Elin Thulin at elin.thulin@devport.se
I am looking forward to read you application!

About DevPort
DevPort is a technology consulting company in an expansive development phase with headquarter in Gothenburg and offices in Stockholm, Linköping, Helsingborg and Karlskrona. DevPort has its core competence in the automotive industry and employs more than 500 people in three business areas - Digital solutions, production development and product development.
We are proud of our employees and of collaborating with several of the world's leading vehicle manufacturers, companies in the defense industry and other development-intensive industries.
We are characterized by a family culture with entrepreneurship, competence, security and a community that infuses the company's operations and contributes to a pleasant and inspiring workplace.

Title: Data Analyst, Team App & Content
Description:
Six years after our broad launch BookBeat now has over 700 000 paying users and it’s only the beginning of our journey! The best way for us to continue growing and offering the best user experience possible is to keep being leaders in understanding our users' needs. That is why we’re expanding the team with another talented analyst!
Are you looking for an exciting role within a skilled team in a dynamic and fast-moving organisation? Do you enjoy working together within a team to contribute to product development and a maximized user experience? Then we might have the job for you!
Team App and Content
On average our users spend twenty-four hours per month in our app, and one of the reasons to the success of BookBeat is that our app is easy to use and that we provide the most relevant books to our users. While our app team works on the development of our app to make it as user friendly as possible, our content team makes sure that the available books are as inspiring and relevant as possible.
Both these teams are central parts of our organisation and as a Data Analyst your focus will be to support both of them with data-driven and actionable insights. You’ll thus have a central role at BookBeat, supporting the development of the app as well as it's content.
Your role
In your day-to-day work you’ll be working with a variety of tasks that all have the same goal; understanding our users, making data driven decisions and making sure that BookBeat continue to be leading in usability and simplicity. This could involve finding a way of helping our 700 000 users find their next favourite book, or by making sure that the next app feature built is as user-friendly as possible.
The work will involve creating business questions and turning them into insights and actions by applying user data, A/B tests etc. You’ll be analysing large sources of user data to make recommendations of new features, building automated content in the app and creating BI reports for follow-up on user behaviour and central KPIs.
Since the insights created will need to be shared in the organization this role requires good communication skills. Therefore, you should enjoy sharing information and supporting an insights-led culture. To be successful in the role we also think that you enjoy taking projects from start to finish.
In this role, you’ll be working close to other data analysts, data scientists, data engineers but also our app team and content team.
We’re looking for someone that:
has an education within a quantitative field such as mathematics, statistics, economics or similar
has a genuine interest in understanding our users and their behaviour
has experience in translating data and statistics into insights, and want to make progress in how to best track our users' behaviour
likes inventing new and helpful ways of visualizing data and might have experience with tools such as Power Bi, Tableau, ggplot etc.
likes working cross functionally in a fast-moving organization
is used to working in SQL
communicates fluently in Swedish and English in speech and writing. Other language skills (e.g. German, Finnish, Polish, French, Spanish, Dutch or Danish) is a bonus!
It’s also nice if you:
have experience or interest in Python or R
If you have any questions, please contact Jeanette Löfgren, jeanette.lofgren@bookbeat.com.
As an employee of BookBeat AB, you can enjoy a benefit package that includes the following:
30 days of vacation each year
ITP1 occupational pension
Occupational group life insurance, work injury insurance & business travel insurance
Yearly wellness allowance
‍️ Weekly wellness hour
Working equipment (computer and phone) as well as phone subscription
BookBeat subscription
In addition to our benefits, we’ll also provide you with:
A stable and sustainable work-life balance (we use flex time)
An office located in the heart of Stockholm
‍️ … including access to a full gym complete with a sauna! We also arrange other fun wellness activities, such as our own running club
The opportunity to grow in your role and career, including challenging & educational work tasks as well as opportunities for education
Fun activities together with colleagues! At BookBeat you’ll enjoy weekly Friday afternoon mingles, monthly company breakfasts and other work events such as Holiday & summer parties, and frequent company wide events
The opportunity to explore projects that you might not have time to do in your day-to-day work during Hack Days
Knowledge sharing opportunities, e.g. during our weekly Friday demo where different teams share what they’ve been or will be working on. Knowledge sharing is also an integral part of our everyday work
(Last but definitely not least) A wonderful and skilled team and manager that will support you throughout your employment!
About us
In 2015, we began our journey towards the goal of offering Europe’s leading service for digital books and in 2016, we launched to the public. Now, about 7 years since our broad launch, BookBeat is used by over 700 000 users every month. We are an ever-growing company within the Bonnier Group and all members who join our journey have the possibility to make an impact on our development – both in the short and long run.
Today, Team BookBeat consists of 150 curious and committed doers. Are you interested in becoming part of our team? Wonderful! While our employees are experts at many different areas, we have four core values uniting all of us:

Be great at what you do
Share what you know
Curiosity for our users and us
Build Team BookBeat
In other words: we want our employees to continuously deep dive into and develop within their area(s) of expertise, but also to share that knowledge with their colleagues – we’re all in this together and cooperate (most often a lot) on a daily basis! We’re also looking for employees who are genuinely curious about our users, journey and organization, a curiosity that drives us to always test out new things in our service and to let our users show us if we’re on the right track. Last but definitely not least we want all our employees to contribute to the everyday cooperations and the wellbeing of Team BookBeat – as already mentioned, we’re in this together and we want our team to be healthy and happy at work, and we all contribute to this in different ways.

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Stockholm, Gothenburg, or Malmö
Posted: 2022-03-27
About the Role
Build Measure Learn Sweden is looking to expand with a Senior Data Analyst to join a team at one of our customers. We are a data & analytics consulting company that is expanding to meet market demand (assignments at clients) and to achieve our mission of playing an impactful part in helping companies in Sweden on their journey to become data-driven.

Are you skilled in the area of data & analytics and feel that it is time to shift context to continue your growth? Would you like colleagues that are best-in-class and humble about it? We will find a great match between you and assignment where both you and the client benefit. Our clients are in need of help in having data guide their decisions, democratizing data and using data to power everything.

We seek you that love everything about data. You have no problem diving into data; cleaning it, transforming it, analyzing it, visualizing it, and using it to tell stories. You want to develop your career at a growing company and work with a massive amount of data-points.
What you'll do
Solve various problems for clients, making an impact across unlimited domains and industries (digital products, banking, insurance, finance, health, e-commerce, marketing, etc.)
Deliver business value by working hands-on cleaning, analyzing, and transforming raw data into insightful findings
Track, analyse and report key metrics & insights to stakeholders on a regular basis
Collaborate with customers Data Analytics & Science teams during projects
Analyze billions of mobile and digital messaging data points
Audit and ensure data quality
Help our customers in becoming more data literate
Run & facilitate workshops
Who you are
3 - 7+ years of experience in Data Analysis - transforming raw data into insightful stories
Programming skills that allow you to be self-sufficient in handling data (Python, SQL)
Knowledge of one or more business domains
In-depth knowledge and hands-on experience with one or more data and analytics technologies (Looker, Tableau, Power Bi, Amplitude or similar)
Knowledge of advanced statistical analysis techniques
Experience working within an Agile team
Experience in working with senior business and IT stakeholders, as well as end-users
Specialisation in digital/marketing analytics, product analytics or business analytics
Ability to take ownership for the end result and to help others to get there
Fast learner, self-starter and intellectually curious
Fluent in English
Ideally you will have
Solid knowledge of the data and analytics landscape and recent trends
Experience running A/B tests & Conversion Rate Optimization
Experience working with Customer Analytics
Degree from university (or equivalent) preferably with a focus on Statistics, Economics, Business, Computer Science or similar
Based near Stockholm or Gothenburg (or willing to relocate to Gothenburg or Stockholm)

Bonus points for:
Experience building data and analytics organizations
Familiar or skilled with machine learning
Why join us?
Interesting and forward-looking assignments within fintechs, e-commerce companies and digital startups / scale-ups
Collaborative, transparent, creative and fun loving culture which you will be involved in shaping
Opportunities for personal and professional growth
Investment in your competence development in latest skills & technologies
An international team (including our partner network) ~6 nationalities so far
Competitive salary
Learning & sharing environment - colleagues skilled in their areas and that enjoy knowledge sharing
Have a mid/long term plan of becoming a freelancer? We'd like to be a part of that and help you towards that goal.
Company parties & team activities
How to apply
If you fit the description above, we’d love to hear from you! Email us at: jobs@buildmeasurelearn.se

We’re looking forward to your application!

Title: Data Analyst for R&D Validation
Description:
Northvolt is now looking for a Data Analyst to be part of our growing validation team in Västerås. This is your chance to contribute to the development of the world's greenest and most sustainable Li-ion battery cell!
The Validation team is working directly with the customer projects and cell development to ensure the excellent performance & safety of Northvolts products – the batteries. Increasing amount of test demands especially in performance and life testing generate huge amounts of data, which need to be processed, visualized, and summarized.
As a Data Analyst for validation, you will be providing data analysis tools (in python) for validation, support with data visualization and generated automated data summaries. You will be collaborating closely with Northvolt’s data team to ensure efficient usage of the generated data.
Key responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Create visualizations and reports validating the performance of our lithium-ion cells
Develop data analysis standards and tools for automated analysis
Share knowledge in collaborative data analysis using modern data science tooling, growing the entire team
Collaborate with Data Engineers to design and implement a data lifecycle for the Validation Engineering application
Ideally, you have gathered first knowledge about battery testing or battery data analysis related to automotive industry or similar. You like to work and communicate with colleagues from various backgrounds. You have an eye for detail, while at the same time keeping the larger picture in sight. You are organized, pragmatic and keep an overview when working on different tasks. You are a curious, passionate life-long learner, who takes ownership and is eager to collaborate to improve the ways of data handling.
The Data Analyst is a vital member of the R&D team and key to Northvolt's mission to enable the future of energy.
Apply with an English CV and your complete LinkedIn profile.
Full-time employment, fixed salary.
The planned starting date is ASAP.
Skills & Requirements
Qualifications/education/experience
Degree in engineering, natural science, or similar field
Engineering foundation with understanding in electrical, mechanical, and chemical domains
Preferable experience from industry (working in a team with multiple stakeholders), including experience in developing code for others
Excellent communication skills with multiple team members.
Specific skills (eg specific programms, languages, certifications etc.)
Excellent English written and oral communication skills.
Python: Data analysis and visualization (jupyter, pandas, matplotlib/seaborn/bokeh/plotly etc.)
Comfortable using version control (e.g. git)
Data storage, processing, and computing technologies
Analytic thinking & understanding of technical correlations
Strong sense of responsibility, and ownership
Strong organization skills and used to manage a range of activities simultaneously
Have plenty of grit, a can-do attitude, an entrepreneurial spirit, a great eye for detail, a sense of humor and a curious mind
Passionate & purpose driven
Bonus Points:
Familiarity with data storage technologies (SQL DB, GCS/S3)
Experience with ERP-systems
Familiarity with Automotive Development Processes
Knowledge of battery industry is an advantage
Experience in multicultural, start-up environment
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment
Fast paced & entrepreneurial culture
Warrant program
Wellness grant

Title: Senior Data Analyst
Description:
Rovio's Stockholm Studio is the studio behind the hugely popular Angry Birds 2, the bigger, badder and birdier sequel to the global phenomenon Angry Birds. The studio is dedicated to making the Angry Birds 2 game experience ever more exciting for players, developing continual improvements, as well as running world class live ops every day.

In addition to Angry Birds 2, Stockholm studio is actively developing new titles with the Angry Birds brand as well as new original IPs. Our approach is to focus on highly accessible yet innovative cores paired with Rovio's light-hearted aesthetic. At the same time, we still aim to deliver a deep meta that can keep players engaged for decades. Our development is driven by our players as we push to become masters of our genre. We use data to provide insights into our players' needs, and we always strive for improvement through continual iteration.

Our ambitious teams are full of passionate gamers who are eager to leave their mark.

Coming into this role, you will build an understanding of the game, players and different business levers such as user acquisition and use that knowledge to build new game features, optimise existing ones and structure vague problem statements in collaboration with stakeholders such as product manager, designers, producers, and UA managers.

You will bring an objective perspective to all phases of decision making by leveraging strong technical skills to mine raw data for valuable information. Finally, we hope that you are a curious team player who is motivated and wants to have fun with data because at the end of the day we are a casual gaming studio, where we strive to have an environment that is fun and enjoyable while at the same time enables you to grow professionally.
What your days will look like:
User Acquisition - Evaluating and understanding the quality of our players and user acquisition activities to recommend optimised ROI strategies
Liveops - Supporting the team with recommendations based on data we collect, answering the team’s questions
Experiments - Designing and running in-game experiments. Helping the team to find options leading to better game monetization performance and our audience satisfaction
Data Exploration - Digging data we collect and looking for opportunities to improve gameplay experience and UA activities.
Collaboration - Working closely with peer Data Analysts, Product Managers, Project Leads and UA managers to continuously improve how we are interpreting game metrics and making decisions

What we think is needed to thrive in this role:
Experience in user acquisition and mobile app marketing
Highly proficient in SQL
Proficiency in scripting languages such as Python or R
Solid understanding of statistics
Experience in product analysis and experiments design (A/B testing, etc.)
Excellent written and verbal communication skills
Presentation and collaboration skills, when you are used to presenting data and providing actionable recommendations to senior stakeholders.
Prio experience in mobile F2P games will definitely help you become productive quicker but is not an absolute must

Recruitment process:
First call: you will have a chance to meet the hiring manager. It will be a first conversation for you to understand the role better and for us to see what motivates you and how you see yourself in the data space.
Take home test: we will ask you to do an assignment at home that we use to assess your technical knowledge and problem solving. If the solution satisfies the requirements we will invite you to present it to the team and discuss it deeper. It is also a chance for you to meet more of your future colleagues.
Final round: a meeting with one of the game producers to evaluate your stakeholder management skills and how you fit into the bigger team.

Data is at the heart of everything we do at Rovio. It enables us to continually improve our games and provide incredible experiences for the millions of users who play our games every day. All of this data is only valuable if it can be used to guide our day to day operations. It is the job of Rovio data craft to turn that raw data into actionable insights for Rovio’s games teams and other business units. The data craft aims to empower Rovio’s teams with insightful data, and also with relevant tools and models that support decision making.

-
We welcome applicants to use the name they want to be addressed by in the application form, regardless of whether it is their legal name.

What to expect when you join us
Meet the Rovians
About Rovio

Title: Project Manager Data Analyst till Varberg Energi
Description:
Varberg Energi är en energi- och IT-koncern som ägs av Varberg kommun genom Varbergs Stadshus AB. Vi är idag drygt 120 anställda och omsatte under 2021 cirka 1,2 miljarder kronor. Våra verksamhetsgrenar är el, fjärrvärme, elhandel, belysning, gas, energitjänster och stadsnät/IoT. Vår omtanke om miljön innebär satsningar på egen produktion av förnybar energi. Läs mer på [www.varbergenergi.se ] (http://www.varbergenergi.se)
Vill du göra skillnad på riktigt? Drivs du av innovation, leda utveckling inom ditt område och vill bara med att skapa lösningar som förändrar energimarknaden? Då tror vi du kommer att söka den här tjänsten
Varberg Energi har länge varit i framkant inom energilösningar. Nu strävar vi efter att bli kundernas favorit i att kunna koppla upp batterier, solpaneler, elbilar och andra energiresurser via våra digitala plattformar. Det är där du kommer in och kan bidra till att vi når dit!

OM ROLLEN
Du kommer dagligen vara med och skapa lösningar som bidrar till ett hållbart samhälle. Det gör du genom att vara ansvarig för och leda vår utveckling av dataanalys baserat på data från kunder, interna system och produktionsanläggningar. Som ansvarig för dataanalys är du den som leder utvecklingen av hur vi på bästa sätt använder all den data som vi har tillgång till från interna IT-system, till externa energiresurser och digitala kundgränssnitt. Du är den som transformerar komplexa data till användbara insikter för våra kunder och för oss själva. I rollen som Project Manager Data Analyst kommer du att arbeta tätt tillsammans med våra ansvariga för digital verksamhetsutveckling och affärsutveckling.

VEM ÄR DU?
Vi tror att du erfarenhet av att arbeta med att transformera data till beslut. Du har en akademisk bakgrund inom systemvetenskap med en styrka inom statistik eller matematik.
Du har kunskap om hur man använder data för att utveckla affärer och beslutsfattande
Erfarenhet av att hela analysprocessen. Inhämta data från olika källor, databearbetning, analys, dela insikter, rådgivning och underlag för beslut
Erfarenhet från tillexempel Microsoft BI, SQL, Python, Mat lab,
Du har förmåga att formulera en hypotes utifrån den data som du har tillgänglig
Du har förmågan att berätta ”historier” där du visualiserar data för att presentera fakta
Du är intresserad av att använda data för att utveckla nya tjänster


VI ERBJUDER
Vi erbjuder ett spännande arbete i ett företag som har ambitionen att ligga långt fram och med målsättningen att alltid möta våra kunders behov. En öppen och prestigelös arbetsplats där du ges goda möjligheter till utveckling. Vi stödjer distansarbete, flera av oss som arbetar här bor i såväl Göteborg, Varberg som Halmstad. Vi har förmånliga erbjudanden till dig som anställd i form av friskvård, flexibel ledighet, sjukvårdsförsäkring och pension.

ANSÖKAN/KONTAKT
Vi samarbetar med rekryteringsföretaget Your Talent i denna rekrytering. Ansök på www.yourtalent.se För ytterligare information om tjänsten vänligen kontakta rekryteringskonsult Johan Sjöberg på 0761-709851 johan.sjoberg@yourtalent.se
Vi arbetar med löpande urval vilket gör att vi gärna tar emot din ansökan snarast möjligt!

Title: Credit Risk Data Analyst to Entercard
Description:
Do you want to work with engaged colleagues in an international environment? Are you result-oriented with the ability to interact and coordinate activities with stakeholders across the organization? Entercard is now looking for their next Credit Risk Data Analyst. Do you have previous experience within quantitative analysis from a bank or financial institution? Then you can be the one we are looking for!
About the role
As a data analyst in consumer loans you will be a part of a team of 7 members who you will work closest with and you will be a part of the larger Credit risk analytics team which consists of over 30 analysts. You will work closely together with credit risk and consumer loans in the Nordic countries. Apart from working with your team, in this role you will cooperate with other functions at Entercard, for example the Commission-, Commercial, Fraud-and Operations team as well as the Finance team.
You are offered
A dynamic work environment with engaged colleagues and varied tasks
Working with colleagues with 40 different nationalities
A solid introduction to Entercard as a company as well as your role. You will be assigned a “buddy” that will be responsible for you during your first weeks to secure a good integration into the team.
Job duties
In this role, you will work towards the Norwegian market with analyzing and processing data towards consumer loans. The employees in the team are passionate about data and their market while supporting their closest colleagues with other markets as well when needed. You will also have ownership of all the analytics for Norway consumer loans, in the long term. You will work with both new and current customers.
The role is various, but a regular day could include working on a strategy, evaluate data and investigate areas of profitability and the impact on the organization. Entercard works with their own data and therefore they are not limited to use the data in a certain way, you are therefore able to use the data to try different ways and evaluating what impact it will have on the organization. After evaluating the data, you will present it.
We are looking for
A University degree in relevant field, e.g., Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Statistics, Engineering or equivalent
Previous work experience of quantitative analysis from a bank or financial institution or as a consultant, preferably with exposure to consumer financing
Strong programming skills in SAS or similar
Strong verbal and written communication skills in English. Knowledge in the Swedish language is seen as a bonus.
As a person you can take ownership and drive your tasks while also being a team player. You are comfortable to challenge and be challenged by your colleagues. You have strong analytical skills and enjoy quantitative work. You are curious and have a structured way of working.
In this recruitment, we will also place great emphasis on your personal skills. The competencies we see as particularly important are:
Result oriented
Cooperative
Quality oriented
Innovative
Other information
Start: According to agreement
Location: Stockholm
Information about the recruitment process
Telephone interview with Academic Work (15 min)
Evidence-based interview with Academic Work (approx. 1 hour)
Interview with Entercard + Case
Second interview with Entercard
Reference making + decision
This recruitment process is conducted by Academic Work. Our selection process is continuous and the advert may close before the recruitment process is completed if we have moved forward to the screening or interview phase.
We do not accept applications via email, but if you have specific questions about the service, these are answered at stn05@academicwork.se during office hours.
Client information
Entercard is one of Scandinavia's leading consumer credit companies with over 2 million customers in three markets. Through our two owners, Barclays and Swedbank, we get access to global and unique expertise within lending. Our goal is to make our customers everyday lives easier by offering smart and responsible payment and financing solutions.

Title: LIA / Internship
Description:
What is this about?
Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions. We understand how Computer Vision and AI can benefit the society. We stand ready to use our expertise to facilitate businesses in their journey into the era of AI. We work with several clients with various industry fields in close collaboration with top universities in Sweden.

Synteda is actively working on several unique products and solutions in various fields. Dream-innovate-create is our work process were our ideas go through different stages. We create successful solutions by checking feasibility of our product idea (POC) and develop our solution working with agile methodologies until we reach a complete full-scale product.

Synteda has a core team of highly qualified experts that provide assessment to identify challenges and explore different ideas to enhance effectiveness and develop specific algorithms to overcome company challenges. Synteda is built on ethical awareness, curiosity, transparency, respect, participation and last but not least science.

Synteda are growing rapidly and we are looking for a talented data analyst to join our team of experts. You are an analytical thinker and detail-oriented who enjoy data mining and continuously want to find a better solution.

Do you want to turn academic knowledge into hands-on digital experience?
Yes, you found the right place. At Synteda you will be able to work in a startup environment, take great responsibility and the opportunity to grow together with the rest of us in the team. You get to work with colleagues who have worked with pioneering research and apply it in practice.

Our team consists senior researchers in the AI field, business developers, and UX designers.
Turn in your application, and get to know us, and allow yourself to embrace an exciting digital journey.

Examples of tasks:
Planning, development, improvement and testing of existing products and present insights to stakeholders.

What are we looking for?
Are currently studying within the AI spectrum of data management, computer vision, data science. We also include students studying C#/ .NET and Java-development.

As a person:
You can communicate effectively with the rest of your team.

Title: Data Analyst - Digital Marketing - LIA Praktik Intern
Description:
Företagsbeskrivning
Cairy AB lanserades år 2019 och har idag den största digitala produkten mot missbruk i Sveriges. Vi befinner oss i stark tillväxt och kommer inom kort att bredda oss till den internationella marknaden.
Kärnan i Cairy består av en app innehållande ett socialt community, anonyma ljudrum, ett program, övningar etc. Vi vill sänka tröskeln så lågt det bara går för att människor i behov av hjälp ska kunna få det. Vårt mission är att bryta den generationstrauma som missbruket för med sig.
Jobbeskrivning
Vi lägger stor vikt i att du ska vinna nya kunskaper inom området och känna dig som en del av vårt härliga team.
Praktikupplägg Dataanalytiker
Du kommer att arbeta över alla våra marknadsföringskanaler för att hjälpa Cairy att förstå avkastningen på investeringen över hela vår marknadsföringsinvestering, från första till sista kronan som spenderas.
Exempel på uppdrag:
- Undersöka avvisningsfrekvenser, genomsnittliga besökstider, sidor per besök, ålders- och könsfördelning
- Samla in mejl från influencers, skribenter och redaktörer vi behöver kontakta
- Övervaka dagliga prestationer, identifiera trender och rapportera om dem
- Analysera resultatet av marknadsföringskampanjer och ge rekommendationer för framtida kampanjer
- Ge strategisk riktning för reklamkampanjer
Som praktikant rapporterar du till Marknadsansvarig eller utsedd handledare.
Kvalifikationer:
Vi söker dig som är student och söker praktikplats om minst 8 veckor på heltid. Det är viktigt att du har goda IT-kunskaper. Ett intresse för appar är ett plus. Som person är du noggrann och effektiv.
Svenska är ett krav då vår kommunikation utåt är på svenska.
Vi erbjuder:
En spännande praktikplats i ett företag som hjälper människor och vill förändra världen till det bättre
Möjlighet till extrajobb efter väl genomförd praktik
Möjlighet till anställning och karriär inom företaget
Upplägg och ansökan:
- Placering: Göteborg, Stockholm och Online. Möjlighet att praktisera helt på distans.
VIKTIGT! ⬇
Bifogas i ansökan: CV och personligt brev
Ange i din ansökan: Datum för praktiken
Kontakt & frågor: Natalie Andersson, Marknadsansvarig
Observera att praktiken är oavlönad.
Som ett led i att säkerställa hög kvalitet på våra rekryteringsprocesser genomför vi tester och referenstagning.
Arbeta på distans
Ja
Jobbtyp: Heltid, Praktik
Arbetstider:
Måndag till fredag
Förmåner:
Jobba hemifrån

Title: Tax Data Analyst
Description:
Nasdaq is now looking for a Tax/Transfer Pricing Data Technology Analyst to join the global Tax team. In this role, you will work mainly with Transfer Pricing, being involved in implementing and improving data processes and technology related to Transfer Pricing and Tax within Nasdaq.
The position is located in Stockholm, Sweden.
Nasdaq has business operations in over 30 countries, and we expand our business through organic growth and acquisitions worldwide. Being part of the international Tax team means you will work closely with colleagues in Stockholm, New York, Bangalore and Sydney as well as with the Business and Accounting teams.
About Nasdaq
Nasdaq is a leading global provider of trading, clearing, exchange technology, listing, information and public company services across six continents. Our technology powers more than 90 marketplaces in 50 countries.
Here, you will work for a global tech leader committed to breaking down barriers to inclusive prosperity. We see technology as a way to allow people to work together more productively and effectively by centralizing data, analytics, and market intelligence.
We’re committed to building a more diverse and inclusive workforce. Not only is it our responsibility to do better, but we also need representative voices to power the fresh thinking that is vital for our business and our clients.
Role and Responsibilities
To be successful in this position, you must have an interest in data, processes and technology and like to translate that in to the exciting world of transfer pricing. We hope you are keen to analyze our tax data! You will be involved in identifying opportunities to improve processes related to tax/accounting information.
You Will Bring
Bachelor of Science degree in business administration, accounting, computer science, data science or equivalent
2-5 years of professional experience within transfer pricing, tax or financial accounting from an international organization
Expertise in Microsoft Office Products, excellent skills in Microsoft Excel
You should be an analytical and ambitious person, who can work independently
Good communication skills in written and spoken English
Would be great if you have
Proficiency with any of the accounting systems, Workday Financials or Hyperion Essbase (SmartView)
Some experience with data transformation tools such as Power BI, Alteryx
Some experience with operational tax/transfer pricing technology products such as Longview
Does This Sound Like You?
We offer a full-time position located in Stockholm, Sweden. As we will start reviewing resumes February 1st, please submit your application in English as soon as possible.
At Nasdaq, we provide our employees with the resources and opportunities they need to chart a career of achievement along with a strong compensation package that includes annual bonus opportunity, equity grants, as well as an employee stock purchase program. Nasdaq Sweden provides its employees 32 days of annual vacation (plus 1 additional flex day every two months), health insurance, career development programs, and more. We advocate flexible ways of working and have a hybrid work model.
Come as You Are
Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Paradox puts the player in focus and we need Data Analysts to do that. Do you want to join us on our journey?
We are looking for a Data Analyst to join the Data, Analytics & BI department. As a member of the Analytics team you will work closely with the product/marketing teams to help them become truly data-driven. You will also support high impact business decisions by analyzing external and internal data and producing reports and visualizations.
On a day-to-day basis you will work with our digital marketing teams and support them with insights based on quantitative data generated by our users. You’ll function as the data specialist, proactively working with stakeholders to support business decisions and evangelizing a data-driven culture at Paradox.

Some of your key responsibilities are:
Function as a specialist to our digital marketing teams, promoting data-driven development in our digital channels (web, email).
Interprets and analyzes data using exploratory mathematic and statistical techniques based on the scientific method.
Responsible for tracking, reporting, and analyzing the performance of marketing activities, ad-hoc analytic requests, and development of dashboards in Tableau/GA.
Design and interpret results of A/B tests to continuously improve conversion and retention.

To be able to do a good job we expect the following from you
Experience working with business, digital or marketing analytics.
M.Sc. or other higher education in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science or similar.
Experience of using web analytics tools, SQL as well as R/Python.

We will consider the following as a plus
Experience from the gaming industry or with digital products
A great passion and interest in gaming and Paradox games in particular.

If you think that this description matches your background, we highly encourage you to apply as soon as possible as we will interview candidates continuously for this position. In your application, please show us why your previous experiences and skills would work for this role and why you are interested in working at Paradox.
Since we strive for a diverse workplace, we highly encourage anyone, no matter who you are, to apply for this job if you think that you'd be able to come into this position if you think you’d be a great fit."

Title: Senior Data Scientist to Greenely
Description:
Greenely is on a mission to create the best customer experience for the modern energy consumer by using technology. We are a digital energy provider that helps people reduce their electricity costs by optimizing their home and car's electricity usage with smart technology in an app!
We are now looking for a Data Scientist who wants to be a part of our journey to make the world more sustainable and help consumers to reduce their energy usage!
The opportunity

We are looking for a Senior Data Scientist to help the company and the product grow. As a Senior Data Scientist, you will be responsible for analyzing large data sets and finding patterns to help Greenely's business achieve its goals.

Your challenge

Your daily work includes:
Identify valuable data sources
Analyze large amounts of information to discover trends and patterns
Build predictive models and machine-learning algorithms
Present information using data visualization techniques
Propose solutions and strategies to business challenges
Coordinate with different teams (ex., product development teams) to implement and monitor outcomes.

Team and workplace

You will be collaborating with the product teams to analyze data and build predictive models. You will also have the opportunity to help and be part of a growing team of data scientists.
Our office is located at Vasagatan 40 in central Stockholm and we apply a hybrid workplace solution.

About you

To be successful in this role, we believe you have proven experience as a Data Scientist or Data Analyst. You have excellent communication and presentation skills and you do also have:
Experience in SQL, Python, and R
Understanding of machine learning and operations research
Strong math skills
Experience with predictive modeling
Experience using business intelligence tools (Ex. Tableau)
Master’s or Ph.D. in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science, or similar fields

It is meritorious if you also have experience in other program languages and experience analyzing data from 3rd party providers such as Google, Facebook Insights, etc. We do also see it as a plus if you have experience with Snowflake and Tableau.

About Greenely
Greenely is on a mission to create the best customer experience for the modern energy consumer by using technology. We are a digital energy provider, helping people to lower their electricity costs by optimizing their home’s and car’s electricity usage with smart technology in an app. Greenely, backed by Nordic venture capital firms, is on a mission to enable households across the world to connect, control and optimize their energy usage. We ultimately believe that the best electricity is the one that is not being used at all, both for the wallet and the planet!

Title: Product Manager
Description:
PinMeTo helps businesses get discovered, found, and verified on the biggest search, map, and social media platforms.
Our online Software as a Service (SaaS) platform makes sure all of a chain or franchise’s locations can be found on multiple search, map, and social media platforms, including Apple, Facebook, Google, Instagram, Twitter, Foursquare, and many more.
We look for product managers that can work as part of an empowered product team to solve our customers problems in a way that works for our business. Our product teams are cross-functional and durable, generally composed of a product manager, a product designer, and several engineers all co-located in our office in Malmö.
You are passionate about solving hard problems for our customers and businesses that ends up in a product that solves our users' problems in a way they love.
While the product designer is accountable for ensuring the solution is usable, and the engineers are accountable for ensuring the solution is feasible, the product manager is accountable for ensuring the solution is both valuable and viable.
We empower our product teams to figure out the best solution to the problems that need to be solved.
Key responsibilities
Be able to influence your teammates, as well as colleagues, stakeholders, and key executives, through your use of data and logic.
Ensuring the solution is both valuable and viable
Collaborate closely with product designer and engineers to discover effective solutions
Making sure that the solution that is delivered is working for our customers and our business
Track industry trends and the competitive landscape as they pertain to your product
A deep knowledge of our users and customers, and the data about how our customers engage with our products
Knowledge, skills and behaviors required:
Understanding of techniques and methods of modern product discovery, and delivery.
2+ years working on technology-powered products as either a product manager, product designer, engineer, data analyst, data scientist, or user researcher.
Demonstrated ability to understand and learn multiple functional areas of business – engineering, design, finance, sales, and marketing.
Demonstrated ability to figure out solutions to hard problems with many constraints, using sound judgment to assess risks.
Proven ability to engage with engineers, designers, and company leaders in a constructive and collaborative relationship.
In an environment that is filled with skilled and creative colleagues, and a multicultural environment that encourages people to make their ideas happen, you can have an impact like nowhere else. We all help each other to build new skills and best practices through the diversity of our backgrounds and opinions – while having a lot of fun in the process. Do you want to be part of our story and join one of the leading SaaS companies in Europe?
We are looking forward to seeing your application!
About the culture and office
The PinMeTo culture is based on responsibility, inclusiveness, and diversity. We are energetic and in it for the long haul, and we value a healthy life/work balance. The office is located next to Malmö Central Station, near restaurants and public transport.

Title: Engineering Data Analyst
Description:
We are looking to grow the data capability at our first gigafactory in Skellefteå, Sweden. Our factories produce large amounts of heterogenous data that get uploaded to our cloud platform, and are then processed, organized, and ready for analysis. You will partner cross-functionally with the Engineering, Production and Quality teams in Skellefteå to drive data-driven manufacturing operations.
As an Engineering Data Analyst, you will contribute directly to solving problems, lead discovery of insights, and build a shared knowledge base. We strive to use technology and data to co-develop solutions that matter, and welcome applicants from diverse experience levels and backgrounds.
We are searching for someone passionate about using data visualization, statistics, and modeling to tell stories and support decisions. The ideal candidate is a curious life-long learner who takes ownership and is eager to collaborate to build better products. This role is a vital member of the Ett Digitalization team is key to Northvolt's mission to enable the future of energy.
Key responsibilities include
Troubleshoot and root cause issues in the manufacturing operations
Build analytics solutions for production, quality, and engineering applications to drive Continuous Improvement projects
Validate generated data and drive data quality initiatives
Share knowledge of data tooling, dataset and analytics capabilities across technical and non-technical teams on-site in Skellefteå
Define requirements for enhancements of the Northvolt Data Science and Analytics Platform
Skills & Requirements
Preferred Experience
Communication, communication, communication. You communicate fluently and humbly with all types of different humans choosing effective methods based on context, audience and purpose.
Python: Data analysis and visualization (jupyter, pandas, matplotlib/seaborn/bokeh/plotly etc.)
Comfortable writing SQL queries
Not Required (bonus points)
[Bonus] Engineering foundation understanding (electro/mechanical/chemical/physical), preferably within the energy domain
[Bonus] Manufacture industry and/or Li-ion technology experience
[Bonus] Statistics, algorithms, clustering, uncertainty quantification
[Bonus] Analyzing and modeling time-series data and unstructured data
[Bonus] Data visualization using tools (e.g. Grafana, Kibana, PowerBI, Tableau, Qlik, Quicksight, etc.)
[Bonus] Software engineering (version control, unix, software workflow, either of C/C++/C#/Java/Go)
[Bonus] Cloud (AWS/GCP/Azure): Data storage, processing, and compute technologies
Skills
Excellent English written and oral communication skills
Independent, organized and entrepreneurial
Passionate team collaborator that can thrive in a diverse international environment (110+ nationalities and counting)
Qualities that we value are flexibility, sense of quality, friendliness, motivation to take on new challenges, grit and a sense of humor
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment
Fast paced & entrepreneurial culture
Warrant program
Wellness grant

Title: Supply and demand planning internship
Description:
Why become a Danone Intern?
By doing an internship with us you have chance to work and learn in a purpose driven and fast-moving international environment. In line with our values, we foster a friendly, motivating, and supportive culture where everyone is a leader, no matter what your position is within our organization. We encourage an entrepreneurial mind-set by giving our employees and interns alike the opportunity to drive growth of strong brands, contribute to a healthier world as well as develop professionally and personally.
This internship
You will work cross functional together with our Supply and Demand Planning teams with their daily routines. You will support our data analyst with providing essential KPIs to the organization. You will get the opportunity to analyze our main processes and monitor and control our warehouse stocks.
Support with Service Level and out of stock reporting
Support in portfolio optimization and waste reduction programs
Support with innovations and promotions execution
Analyzing and mapping out key processes and identifying areas of improvement
Inventory management related topics
About you:
Currently pursuing a degree in Supply Chain Management
Have an internship period included in your program
Available for at least 10 weeks during Spring 2023
Profound English skills
Very good Excel skills
Good process understanding
Kindly note that this internship is unpaid. It needs to be connected with a university education or any other type of education that has an internship period planned into the education plan, for example, LiA. Please also be aware that we are unable to provide relocation services for this role.
About us:
Danone’s mission is bringing health through food to as many people as possible and we and we believe in order to do so we need a healthy planet. We have more than 100 000 employees worldwide who all strive for our vision One Planet One Health.
Danone Nordics & Baltics have 500 employees based in Sweden, Finland, Denmark, Norway, Latvia and Lithuania. Our brand portfolio includes many trusted brands such as Alpro, Activia, Actimel, Danonino, Nutricia and Aqua d´Or. Danone Nordics is also proud to be a B Corp Certificated Company which means we are doing business in a better way.
Kindly send in your application as soon as possible but no later than November 21st. We are interviewing candidates continuously so please note that the opening may be closed prior to the last application day.
Danone AB with its registered office in Stockholm (Gårdsvägen 14, 169 70 Solna) is the controller of your personal data disclosed in the profile and in documents submitted during the recruitment process.

Title: Data Analyst/BI Developer till spännande konsultbolag
Description:
Vi söker en vass Data Analyst/BI Developer till vår kund som är ett litet konsultbolag specialiserat inom BI och Analytics. På detta bolag är det du som blir stjärnan, det är din utveckling som hamnar i fokus och du har mycket att säga till om vilka uppdrag du kommer ta dig an. Här är det konsulten som är i fokus!
Dina framtida arbetsuppgifter
Som konsult kommer du att arbeta med BI-utveckling och dataanalys i kundernas projekt. Du kommer sätta dig in djupt i kundens behov i relation till data och BI, från att prata med användare, bygga prototyper, sätta dig in i hur datan är lagrad, hämta ut densamma samt bygga visualiseringar i ett BI-system.
Bolaget arbetar med många olika typer av kunder vilket ger möjlighet till uppdrag i många olika branscher och områden. Vilket uppdrag du är på kommer så klart påverka vilka verktyg du kommer hantera. Sannolikt sitter du mycket i SQL och kommer få bredda din kompetens inom BI-verktyg så som Power BI, Tableau, Qlik, etc.
Om du vill vara del av ett litet, familjärt bolag med variationen som en konsultroll erbjuder, men samtidigt med en hög grad av kontroll över vilka uppdrag du kommer ta dig an, är detta platsen för dig! Du kommer vässa din kompetens inom analys och BI och driva projekt och leverera stor nytta till företagets kunder

Vi söker dig som har
Har goda kunskaper i SQL samt minst ett BI-verktyg, så som Power BI, Tableau, Qlik eller liknande
Har byggt rapporter/analyser i ett eller flera verksamhetsområden, t.ex. ekonomirapporter, försäljningsanalys, kundanalys och har erfarenhet av att iterativt ta fram rapport- och analyslösningar med användare
Har goda kunskaper i svenska
Som person trivs du i variation där du får se nya miljöer i form av kundföretagen, samt att snabbt kunna sätta dig in i dessa och ta ansvar och driva på där det behövs. Du har goda kommunikativa förmågor i att både presentera dig själv för kunderna och dina insights för stakeholders inom organisationen.
Övrig information
T.ex Tjänsten avser heltid, 40h/v. Om du har relevant erfarenhet och är nyfiken på att veta mer, tveka inte att skicka din ansökan så tar vi gärna en vidare dialog!

Title: Senior Quantitative Analyst / Data Analyst
Description:
Vinter is seeking ambitious quantitative analysts to join our team to build and improve index strategies for our institutional customers. At Vinter, you’ll help solve unique, large-scale, and highly complex technical problems. The quantitative analyst is ultimately responsible for the implementation, review, rebalance, and reconstitution of the Vinter index portfolio.
Vinter’s mission is to institutionalize crypto. We create and calculate complex yet elegant crypto indexes used in financial products worldwide. Our customers are some of the most successful crypto funds in the world, and our investors are some of the most well-respected in the industry. We recently raised a $3.4M Series Seed and are now looking to build one of the greatest teams in our industry.
Since our incorporation in 2019, we’ve been listed as a top European startup. Our team is a diverse group of people from over eight countries speaking 13 different languages.
Responsibilities:
As a member of the index team, you will be responsible for the development of new index algorithms, backtesting reports, periodic Index reviews, and rebalances of the Vinter indexes. Key areas of responsibility will include:
Develop new index algorithms and investment strategies.
Automate the company's backtesting infrastructure and develop our capabilities to visualize backtesting results.
Conduct the periodic rebalancing process of indexes and/or the associated implementation of any changes, in accordance with their review schedule.
Develop automated eligibility checks of crypto assets for inclusion in Vinter indexes, such as liquidity and free float.
Conduct data analysis on the results of index calculations to ensure accuracy and quality.
Escalate any issues/concerns to the line manager and report exceptions in a timely manner.
Timely investigation and resolution of any client query relevant to your role and areas of expertise.
Highlight and recommend process improvements to your line manager that will improve the levels of quality, productivity & client service.
Using all available data sources including data vendors, crypto exchanges, public blockchains, and regulatory filings.
Actively contribute to the training and onboarding of new team members.
Requirements:
5+ years of experience in developing and implementing financial or statistical models in a production environment.
Bachelor’s degree.
Understanding of investment management and portfolio construction across asset classes.
Knowledge of performance measurement and portfolio analysis concepts.
Experience in automating analytical processes in a structured manner.
A proven track record for achievement in delivering a high-quality service.
Proficiency in Python, numerical algorithm development, and database management.
Meriting:
MS or MBA in Computer Science, finance, financial engineering, economics, statistics, or other quantitative fields.
Experience from working at a market data provider or index provider.
NB. Vinter will hire you through our entity in the UK and Sweden. In other countries, we hire using a global payroll provider.
Vinter is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversifying its workforce. Accordingly, it is the policy of the Firm to ensure equal employment opportunity without discrimination or harassment based on race, color, religion, creed, age, sex, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, national origin, citizenship, disability, marital and civil partnership/union status, pregnancy or any other characteristic protected by law.

Title: Web Analyst at H&M Business Unit
Description:
Company Description

Welcome to H&M! A workplace where you can be yourself & so much more! We want to make it possible for everyone to look, feel and do good. We take pride in our history of making fashion accessible to everyone and our ambition for tomorrow is to make fashion even more sustainable, inclusive, and welcoming.
Why work at H&M?
H&M is a workplace where you’ll join a global fashion family that combines teamwork with individual expression and gives you the challenges and opportunities that can help you learn, grow, and succeed.
We believe that it’s when you mix and match different talents, experiences, and styles that the real magic happens. That’s why our teams are built with different personalities, talents, and people from all kinds of backgrounds. If you are willing to learn, grow and help our customers and your colleagues, H&M will always be a place for you to both express your individuality and feel like you belong.
We also believe that you can’t change the world without great people on your side. So, we offer all our employees generous benefits, lots of learning opportunities and the possibility to start building a more long-term career. Bring your whole personality to work, stay as long as you want, and grow more than you ever thought was possible. Be yourself & more at H&M.

Job Description

Would you like to elevate how we appeal to our customers in any given timing, touchpoint, and location – by using data as our foundation for all decision making? We are building a world class customer experience team and we need you!
In the role as a Web analyst, you will contribute with decision support through strategic interpretation of data and derived insights. This will help us to set strategies and actions to further develop our world class customer experience, grow our customer base, drive profitable sales and create meaningful relationships with our customers. As a Web Analyst, you will analyze the customer behavior in all our digital channels. You will belong to a business unit customer experience team and collaborate with a big analytics community within the company.
Your responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Support strategy, decision making, prioritization and follow up of initiatives. Derive a full overview of the customer journey on hm.com
Provide a holistic understanding of the customer experience, transactional data and sales performance and proactively identify ways to improve
Identify and optimize key conversion paths, determining the most important KPI’s to track and setting benchmarks
Evaluate commercial strategies, campaigns, and media investments
Build hypotheses based on data and insights to drive A/B testing or multi-variant testing designs
Take part in driving improved web analytics capabilities and building tools, e.g., identify tracking requirements and integration of Google Analytics data into Business intelligence systems

Qualifications

We are looking for a person who is a connector and collaborator who knows how to navigate in a highly complex global environment. You have a self-going personality with a strong sense of responsibility and desire to make an impact. You have a strong entrepreneurial spirit and thrive in a constantly changing environment. We believe you are curious and triggered by improving the customer experience. Finding simple solutions to complex problems.
We would love to meet someone who has/is:
Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience within E-commerce
A degree within marketing, economics, mathematics, engineering or similar
Analytical and keen to find trends, patterns, and true answers to maximize customer experience
Strong experience in web analytics (or similar, CRO, Data analyst) working with different data sets and understanding performance drivers
Experienced in working with Google Analytics and Looker Studio, Tableau, GTM, Tealium, Clicktale or similar
Skilled in analytical programming languages such as Big Query, Python, R, or SQL (preferred)
Meriting to have worked with Optimizely, Content square, HTML, JavaScript or similar
Good experience of creating and delivering periodic reporting for business stakeholders
Beneficial with prior A/B testing experience
What we offer you:
We will offer you a fantastic team with high energy, a lot of creativity and forward-leaning mindset. We are customer & data obsessed and we love fashion. We also give you an environment with a lot of ownership, where we constantly act, learn and adapt - breaking new grounds as a team constantly and find new opportunities to grow and develop our business. You will get a role in the center of attention with a wide range of touch points in global functions, regions, and colleagues from all over the world.

Additional Information

This is a full-time permanent position, starting as soon as possible, based at our head office in Stockholm. If you feel that your experience, skills and ambitions are right for this role, please send your resume in English as soon as possible.
Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page. H&M Group we strive to have a fair and inclusive recruitment process. We kindly ask you to not attach cover letter in your application as they often contain information that can easily trigger unintentional biases.
We look forward to receiving your application!
H&M is committed to creating a Diverse & Inclusive environment and we are actively looking for qualified candidates irrespective of race, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, ethnicity, religion, national origin, disability or age.

Title: Conversion Master Data Analyst to Procter & Gamble
Description:
We are currently looking for a Conversion Master Data Analyst to our exciting customer Procter & Gamble. This is a consultancy opportunity, a 6-month contract starting a soon as possible with the possibility for an extension.The office is located in Stockholm.
About the company:
P&G is a fortune 500 company in the FMCG industry. It is the home of iconic, trusted brands that make every-day life a little bit easier. The insight, innovation and passion of their talented teams has helped them to grow to a global company that supports good causes and protects the environment.
About the role:
As a Conversion Master Data Analyst you will be a part of the Initiative Planning Team and you will focus on executing tasks related to new product launches and product changes. In the role you will be working a lot with SAP and Excel, ensuring master data is updated and set up for the readiness for new launches. The role has two different parts to it – one is actively involved in the daily order cycle meaning the mornings normally are focused on making sure orders runs smoothly in the sense of correct set up. The afternoons are focused on making sure new initiatives are setup correctly for coming initiatives and projects. We expect you to have a continuous improvement mind set. We would like you are collaborative, have good social skills and an analytical mindset. The role suits a person who enjoys working with data across different systems.
Key Responsibilities:
Lead the work to ensure the master data is accurate and timely maintained in the areas of product, customer, billing, and pricing.
Be part of the logistics organization which owns the roll-out of new initiatives (products) in the market, with master data and GDSN (Global Data Synchronization Network) publication being your areas of responsibility.
Partner with different parts of the supply chain organization, including Initiatives Planning, Business Planning, Supply Planning, Customer Operations, and Customer Service where all has connection to part of your responsibilities within master data.
Be part of the process improvements and simplification to support productivity improvements and eliminate waste in the process within your scope.
Working independently and with discipline.

Your Profile:
Qualifications:
BSc or MSc in any discipline, with preference, but not limited to, Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (STEM) and Supply Chain Management degrees.
Ability to solve problems related to master data set up and Order, Shipping Billing processes - identification of issues through to resolution.
Uses own initiative to identify, develop and standardize solutions to simplify and improve processes.
Ability to communicate verbally and in writing and to present material to a diverse audience
Being used to a fast-paced working environment and collaborative
Fast learner and strong sense of ownership.
Technical Skills:
Proficient in SAP, Microsoft Excel, Power BI.
Analytical – able to work with large amounts of data to understand how to drive the business forward
Automations / Robotics would be an advantage
Fluent in English is required
Interested?
If you are up for the challenge and think it suits you, we´d like to hear from you. Apply today, the position might be filled before the application deadline.

Title: Data Officer
Description:
Data Officer
15/11/22McDNFI_1668484809
Data Officer | Power BI | Financial Services

This company helps people and businesses make informed decisions on financial and insurance questions, and now they're further expanding their data team with a Data Specialist to help them on this journey.

They've been dominating this market across the Nordics for many years and have had a real focus to be data-driven to ensure that internal and external stakeholders have the most relevant information and are able to offer the best advice in finance, insurance and wealth management.

The Business Intelligence team's mission is to support colleagues with all things data: databases, advanced analytics and insights, therefor making the right decisions. They develop and manage the central infrastructure for data collection, distribution and presentation; the platform is a cornerstone of the business and what they've achieved on a data and development level - it is crucial for the data-driven culture that they are cultivating.

As the Data Specialist you will have the opportunity to fundamentally influence the design of the advanced analytics and the reach this has across the business.

You will do this by working in a team and contributing to the best-practice, designing and developing solutions independently and there is plenty of opportunity to put your stamp on this way of working. An 'anything is possible' attitude is highly desired so you can be involved in decision-making and taking steps to ensure group's mission to be data-driven is achievable.

Main responsibilities include:

Strengthening the group's data analysis
Collaborating with the business to explore and understand requirement, then translate those into technical solutions
Create and maintain Power BI datasets and reports based on the data in the Azure SQL databases
Help promote successful reports and analysis across the group
Support specific data driven projects and topics by helping supply relevant data, doing analysis and generate insights, often in close collaboration with other group functions

Requirements for the position:

A minimum of 3 years' experience as a BI/Data Analyst
Interest in working with both the business and being technically hands-on
Solid understanding of Power BI, or other front end tools
Knowledge in SQL
Fluent Swedish and English in speech and writing

Data is at the very core of what they do, so if you're passionate about data-driven decisions within the financial market and seeing how data can improve businesses from the inside-out, then this is the place for you.

What else can they offer you?

You will be working in their modern offices in central Stockholm with a hybrid working model and therefore get the chance to work from home and work amongst colleagues.
Working closely with the business and helping to understand what's needed from the data, very much feeling like your work is meaningful.
They have a great culture - everybody is very sociable, friendly and passionate about what they do with lots of knowledge sharing potential.
They're a Microsoft partner
They have the financial strength of an enterprise company but as they have the same successful leadership team from when they first started, they have also great start-up feel (but with genuine structure).
You have trust from day one and that is fed down from the CEO; you are never micro-managed and are given the freedom and trust to work in the best way that you and the team and have decided.

Does this sound like a good fit to your experience and a potentially interesting next step for you? Then apply to this advert and we can schedule in a chat to go into even further depth of how this company is making a difference.

Title: Product Manager - Data Foundations
Description:
Tink was founded in 2012, and a decade later became part of Visa in 2022. Tink was created with the aim of changing the banking industry for the better. We have built Europe’s most robust open banking platform – with the broadest, deepest connectivity and powerful services that create value out of the financial data. We offer the tools that allow anyone – from big banks and fintechs to startups – to build the future of financial services across Europe.
The Data Foundation area fuels our decisions and innovation across all of our products and services by providing a reliable and scalable data platform and tooling. We work across Tink serving a wide range of areas and needs from business insights and product analytics to external reporting, machine learning and data applications. Now is the time to take it to the next level.

In this role, you will be responsible for defining and championing our data strategy and roadmap by managing data platform teams. You will own the tools, infrastructure and processes that allow everyone at Tink to quickly turn data into actionable insights and powerful data products.

We think that you either come from a solid product management background and are excited to venture into the data domain, or that you have been working as a data analyst, data scientist or data engineer and after some exposure to Product Management you are now interested in taking on a new type of role. If you have experience of both, that’s even better.

In this role you will:
Be part of two teams that design, build and operate data flows within Tink’s data platform
Work tirelessly to gain a deep understanding of the needs of your stakeholders - from data scientists and developers in other product teams, to product analysts, customer success managers and finance teams
Define goals and milestones for your teams and work side by side with your team members, the engineering manager and other product teams and stakeholders to ensure the goals are reached
Evaluate and measure the impact of your teams’ work and ensure that it contributes to reaching Tink’s overall goals
Run some of the team's day-to-day activities and ceremonies: retros, standups, groomings and plannings
Communicate overall status to stakeholders


What we’re looking for:
Experience of working either as a product manager or in a data analyst/scientist/engineer role possibly exposed to Product Management
Eagerness to take Tink data and Products to the next level
Constant drive for ensuring your work has a measurable impact on Tink’s business, by continuously looking for ways to validate the value you are creating
High sense of urgency and commitment; we always strive to make things happen
Proven ability to work cross-functionally in a highly collaborative environment
Mindset of looking for pragmatic solutions and balancing quality and time to delivery depending on the situation
Previous experience working with cloud based data platforms such as GCP, AWS or similar
Desire to work in a fast-paced, results-driven environment with multiple responsibilities
Who we are at Tink
We are a company of developers and engineers – it’s in our DNA to imagine, build and iterate. We were founded with a vision of transforming an industry that lacked competition and momentum. And we have built a company of passionate over-achievers who all believe there is always a better way of doing things.
People from all over Europe – and the world – have joined us on our mission to build the biggest and best open banking platform in Europe.
We're looking forward to your application!

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.
For further information see www.babyshop.com
ABOUT THE POSITION
Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.
WHAT YOU'LL DO
Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE
You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...
Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.
