Title: Chief Product Officer
Description:
Contracts are the heart of any business. While the world is undergoing huge digital transformation, contracts are still stuck in the dark ages. Oneflow believes that there’s a better way to work with contracts. One free from friction that flows seamlessly with experience so delightful, it feels like magic.

Oneflow develops an end-to-end SaaS platform for digital contract automation. While the contract automation market is competitive, it’s underserved and our ambition is for Oneflow contracts to become accessible to everyone, the default way of working with contracts.


This is you

You’re a strong leader and an effective coach. You take ownership and responsibility for your teams’ contribution and impact. Your team looks up to you and your visionary way of being, and the leaders can rely on you for coaching and support.

With a commercial mindset, you have the ability to make tough, strategic decisions that develop and execute product strategy towards our vision while delivering value to our customers. Change is natural to you. In fact, you’ve learned from the challenges and have the necessary skills to help your team thrive and grow through changes.

You have a strong technical background, excellent communication and presentation skills, ensuring you have trust in your team and the wider company.

It will be exciting for you to translate Oneflow’s vision into concrete actions, with the ability to influence and enable our future growth journey, all whilst being an excellent cultural contributor to our company.

What you’ll do

As our new CPO, you’ll be part of and work with the management team, and will lead Oneflow’s product portfolio strategy and the company’s product-led-growth journey. You will drive operational excellence with a strong commercial focus and create a strong SaaS product through customer obsession and design.

You will ensure the product development roadmap aligns with the Oneflow’s business goals and strive for the best time to market for our products by working closely with the Oneflow’s CTO, Engineering Managers and other key stakeholders.


Create, oversee and drive the short- and long-term product vision and strategy
Lead and develop product, UX, and data analyst teams, help teams collaborate across cross-functionally, with customers and other stakeholders
Keep abreast of market trends and identify business opportunities within our current and adjacent business segments
Implement and measure product KPIs/OKRs and derive actions plans to meet our company objectives
Grow, coach, and develop our product, UX, and data analyst teams within a fast scaling agile environment


Skills & Requirements
10 years’ experience in CPO/Head of/VP of Product positions with proven record of working with SaaS or subscription based products
Proven ability to build, coach and lead effective teams and leaders in a fast-paced environment
Strong business acumen with a highly analytical mindset
Strong track record in user experience and data-driven-development
Experienced with product/development tools and best practices
Experience in taking strategic decisions, tactical planning all the way to operational execution
Knowledgeable in modern agile methodologies

What’s in it for you
Joining a high-growth scale up with a great culture - our eNPS (employee happiness score) is above industry average
Working in a team with a clear vision, objectives, and key results
Yearly healthcare benefit of 5000 SEK
Well equipped office with snacks and beverages
Weekly/monthly culture based activities
Insurance and pension plan
Highly skilled and inspiring international colleagues
Fast-paced, inclusive, and open work culture
Leave your mark, create your own career path


Come work with us
We value gender equality and diversity in organization, so we strive for a team that reflects the diversity in today's society. At Oneflow we currently have 33 nationalities, with offices in 7 countries, and are proud of an extremely diverse workplace. Our recruitment is based on competence.
Apply by submitting your CV and a personal letter about why this is the role for you. We can’t wait to meet you!
Visit our website for more information about our product and Oneflow. Visit our blog for more information about our culture and future colleagues.

Title: Data Engineer to XLN Audio
Description:
Are you a Data Engineer with a creative mindset ready for new challenges? If the answer is yes, this is a position for you! We are expanding the team with a Data Engineer to help us build the best possible E-commerce experience resulting in inspiring a big community of music creators.

At XLN Audio, we create software for music production and award-winning virtual instruments used worldwide by creative enthusiasts, professional music producers, songwriters and bands. With Max Martin as a co-owner, music studios and instruments at the office ready to use, there is no doubt that we have rhythm in our blood. We love what we do - helping people express themselves through music. Our ambition is to build the world’s most inspiring and innovative software, to help bring ideas to life and be part of the powerful feeling only music can create.
As for the team, we are a bunch of driven, quirky, caring music nerds who never fail to make work fun. We believe that we work better when our lives are balanced, and flexibility is an essential part of our success. We want to ensure everyone can have the best combination of their families – the one at home and the one at XLN. To allow you to be at your most productive and creative self, you also have the opportunity to combine working from the office and remote – wherever it suits you and your work best.

About the role
We are looking for a Data Engineer who will be responsible for maintaining and developing our data collection pipeline and integrations. In this role you will make data accessible to other teams and ensure our data is secured as well as exploring ways to enhance data quality and reliability. As our Data Engineer you will also have the opportunity to identify opportunities for data acquisition and interpret trends and patterns. In this role you will work closely with our Data Analyst and be able to influence the architecture of how we set things up as well as how we work.
We don’t have many legacy systems to deal with and have invested the last year in establishing a modern commercial tech stack. This gives us time to spend on building customer experiences rather than spending time on maintaining integrations. As a team we stay lean and autonomous by being cross functional which enables us to analyse, design, build and launch new features on our own.

As far as the technical competences we believe you have:
1+ years of experience of Data Engineering
A degree in a relevant field
Experience of:
Google Cloud Platform
SQL and Database Management
Python

It’s a big bonus if you have:
Experience in Back End development
Any relevant certifications, such as the Google Data Engineering Certificate

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.
For further information see www.babyshop.com
ABOUT THE POSITION
Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organization, where it acts as the foundation to our everyday work; whether it being more traditional reporting about what has happened, ad-hoc analysis to understand why that happened, or highly complex machine learning models to predict what will happen. We truly believe that one of the key factors of gaining a competitive advantage in a highly competitive market, is through the use of our data. As a Data Engineer, you will join the Data Team consisting of people with different expertise; Data Warehouse Developer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We use a combination of Fivetran and Apache Kafka to load data into our DWH Snowflake as well as DBT for transformation. Here you will get your hands dirty to understand and transform data using SQL for downstream tasks, ranging from analysis, to BI, to advanced ML use-cases. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO
Develop an understanding of source data as well as end-user needs, and use that to transform data into appropriate formats.
Collaborate with the other members of the Data Team to leverage data end-to-end, from discovering and connecting new data sources, load and transform, to be used for use-cases within BI/ML.
Use CI/CD best-practices together with version control to develop our dbt-workflow.
Use SQL best-practices to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, high performant code.

WHO YOU ARE
You have a passion for data & tech and appreciate a fast-paced entrepreneurial start-up vibe.
You have experience with relational databases and an excellent understanding of SQL.
You have experience in database design and modeling for data warehouse and business intelligence applications.
You are interested in keeping up to date with technological advancements within the data field, and are not afraid to try out new tech.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...
Have previous experience with dbt, and dbt Cloud.
Have previous experience with Snowflake.
Have previous experience with CI/CD and version control.
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Data Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.
Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28, however, applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!
Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: DevOps / Data engineer
Description:
About us
Koalitionen is an IT-consultant company that delivers high-quality consultants to a few of Sweden's biggest companies in various industries.

What do we provide?
We are continuously striving to provide the best conditions for our colleagues as well as for our consultants. At Koalitionen we value hard work and always strive to deliver the best possible results to our clients.

Who are we looking for?

We are looking for you who have in-depth competence and interest in DevOps/data engineers. In your role, you work both with the implementation and management of various abilities that belong to the product. You will be the bridge between the Data Scientist, Data Analyst, and the rest of the IT function.

Assignment background
We are looking for a data engineer for Group staff digitization, IOC, platforms, and DevOps who wants to be involved in developing future patient, resident, and employee services. You will contribute by building new abilities and working with service development to better understand and meet the needs and demands of our residents and employee services now and in the future.
Assignment
As a DevOps/data engineer, you will be part of the DevOps team belonging to the department Infrastructure and Cybersecurity, Unit Platforms. Your assignment will involve designing, developing, testing, and maintaining robust, secure, and scalable solutions for the storage and processing of data, using data pipelines and automation. With the guiding principle of "automate everything" you will help create solutions for the deployment of both infrastructure and platform capacity for both internal and external use.

Requirements
Good knowledge of SQL/NoSQL, ETL/ELT development.
Experience building pipelines and automation.
Experience/knowledge in python
Experience with data modeling
Good understanding of DevOps methodology and agile working methods.
Have the ability to express yourself well in speech and writing in both Swedish and English
The position will be security classified, which requires Swedish citizenship
You are welcome to apply whether you are a sub-consultant or are looking to be employed.

Title: Data & AI-kompetens till Karlstad
Description:
Arbetsuppgifter
Data & AI är ett fokuserat satsningsområde inom Sogeti som genomsyrar oss lokalt, nationellt och globalt.
I Karlstad är det ett av våra absoluta satsningsområden. För oss handlar det främst om att skapa möjligheter för våra kunder att fatta bättre affärsbeslut, att förstå kundernas verksamhet och att lösa problem samt fokusera på kundnytta. Vårt främsta fokus är verktyg inom Microsoft-stacken men som alltid är teknik underordnat kundnytta. På Sogeti finner du härliga kollegor med stor erfarenhet och ett nätverk som du kan bidra till och dra nytta av. Det kommer finnas stora möjlighet att påverka vår fortsatta resa inom området både internt och tillsammans med våra kunder.
Som konsult inom Data & AI på Sogeti kommer du att hjälpa våra kunder både genom strategiska och operativa förbättringar. Den här annonsen riktar sig till dig som är t ex Data Engineer , Data Scientist , Data Analyst eller BI-utvecklare.
Du är analytisk , tekniskt skicklig och drivs av att tillsammans med kunden lösa problem och förbättra dess verksamhet. Som person ser vi gärna att du tycker om att arbeta i team samt är drivande och utåtriktad.
Sogeti Karlstad har ett modernt kontor med närhet till spännande kunder och projekt inom hela regionen. Vår arbetsplats präglas av positiv attityd där vi hjälper varandra och har kul på jobbet. Lika viktigt är vår satsning på erfarenhetsutbyte och kompetensutveckling.
Kvalifikationer
Vi söker dig som har erfarenhet inom något av följande:
Big Data, Hadoop, Machine Learning, Data Management, Modern Data Platform, Data Lake, Data Bricks, Azure/Cloud
Business Intelligence-lösningar (med ETL, Data Warehouse, analyskuber och Power BI)
Du talar och skriver flytande svenska och uttrycker dig väl i tal och skrift på engelska.
Du kan ansöka direkt via länken. Det tar bara någon minut och du kan bifoga din LinkedIn-profil.
Välkommen med din ansökan!

Title: Analytics Manager
Description:
About the job

Are you an expert in Procurement and data analytics? And are you able to secure the connection of Procurement to the Analytics Platform, giving us access to a wealth of information? Then you may be our new Analytics Manager!
As an Analytics Manager, you will enable Procurement to work with Vattenfall’s Analytics Platform while improving the solutions we currently have. You will support Procurement and the business with a thorough understanding of the data that we have, with the acquisition of new data and consequently the use of new insights to improve results. And you will be our numbers guru driving the understanding of our Procurement business and driving our value delivery with continuous improvement.
You will provide Procurement with easily accessible information and insights that will support our staff in their daily responsibilities. Next to this, we would like to use available and new data to increase predictability of procurement processes and results with new machine learning-driven technologies. We continuously aim to increase efficiency and effectiveness of Procurement. The Analytics Manager will help us achieve this via smarter usage of data, the implementation of new solutions that will improve our information and insights, via new solutions and new channels.
Your responsibilities:
Being the SPOC for Vattenfall Finance and IT for the connection of Procurement to the Vattenfall Analytics Platform and for improvements to current solutions.
Supporting Procurement on a day-to-day basis with all requests relating to data, information, and insights.
Supporting Procurement on a day-to-day basis with all requests relating to dashboards, performance, and continuous improvement initiatives.
Support Procurement’s Digital Transformation program with project management of all data related activities and with value management as owner of the business case solution for the program.
Work with the data analyst in program and day-to-day business activities and provide guidance and coaching.
Identifying current gaps and omissions and designing solutions for key strategic projects across the business.
Redesign the Procurement Lab into a steady provider of solutions where new (data) technologies are being applied to solve business problems and create business opportunities.
Work together with partner and stakeholders to create a data architecture, and select the right tools to optimize this data landscape incl the tools needed to achieve Procurement goals.
Location
This position could be done from: Stockholm, Amsterdam Berlin or London.

Your profile

Your profile / who are you?
You have extensive experience in Procurement and know source-to-contract and procure-to-pay process in detail (including SAP). You speak data language and can translate the information needs of Procurement to requirements for those working with Procurement Data. Your data engineering and science skills are at a high level, and you are an absolute numbers guru driving the understanding and continuous improvement of what Procurement does. You have strong experience executing this in either an Agile way of working or in traditional project management methodologies, are organized, pro-active and results oriented, with excellent communication and collaboration skills.
Next to this, you recognize yourself in the following:
Minimum of 5 years of experience working in a similar Procurement role or in consultancy in which you helped digital transformations of Procurement, systems implementations and/or worked in the data and analytics space for Procurement connecting Procurement units to Analytics platforms, integrating external data sources, and working with cloud-based solutions.
Extensive knowledge of ERP software (SAP is a must) and Procurement tools in general.
Extensive knowledge of the analytics industry, developments in the industry and application of new technologies for (Procurement) Analytics purposes.
Exceptional problem solving, and modeling skills with ability to synthesize and analyze data to create useful information and concise analysis.
Can work autonomously, to meet tight deadlines, and to thrive in a fast-paced environment under pressure.
Ability to work collaboratively across functions and develop strong relationships with business leaders
Advanced knowledge of Excel, PowerBI, QlikView, Python, SQL and/or other analytical tools. The ability to learn, analyze and implement new systems quickly
Excellent communication skills (both written and verbal) in English

Additional information

Our offer
Good remuneration, a challenging and international work environment, and the possibility to work with some of the best in the field. You will be working in interdisciplinary teams and you can always count on support from committed colleagues. We offer attractive employment conditions and opportunities for personal and professional development.

More Information
We welcome your application in English, no later than the 5th of February. We kindly request that you do not send applications by any means other than via our website as we cannot guarantee that we will be able to process applications that are not made via our website.

For more information about the recruitment process you are welcome to contact our recruiter Stijn van der Kleij via stijn.vanderkleij@vattenfall.com.
At Vattenfall we are convinced that diversity contributes to build a more profitable and attractive company and we strive to be good role model regarding diversity. Vattenfall works actively for all employees to have the same opportunities and rights regardless of gender, ethnicity, age, transgender identity or expression, religion or other belief, disability or sexual orientation.

We look forward to receiving your application!

About the company

Vattenfall is a European energy company with approximately 20 000 employees. For more than 100 years we have electrified industries, supplied energy to people’s homes and modernized our way of living through innovation and cooperation. We now want to make fossil-free living possible within one generation. To be able to reach this ambitious goal we are looking for talented individuals who, in addition to their passion for their own role, also have strong team spirit and want to contribute to supporting a meaningful corporate mission.

Title: Data Analyst till Rocket Revenue
Description:
Har du en passion för att ständigt utveckla och utmana dig själv och företaget? Trivs du i en dynamisk och föränderlig arbetsmiljö? Sök då tjänsten som Data Analyst till Rocket Revenue idag!
OM TJÄNSTEN:
Rocket Revenue växer så det knackar och söker nu efter en motiverad och passionerad person till deras team. Tillsammans med dem söker vi nu efter en Data Analyst. Som en del av teamet kommer du ansvara för implementeringsprojekt, identifiera nya affärsmöjligheter, handleda juniora kollegor i teamet samt ta dig an deras med komplexa kundsamarbeten. Du kommer vidare arbeta mer strategiskt genom att leda kunden mot att bygga en datadriven organisation med rätt uppsättning spårningar, KPI: er, processer och verktyg.
ARBETSUPPGIFTER:
Arbeta med bolagets mest komplexa projekt, göra det möjligt för deras kunder att få maximalt värde från sina analysplattformar
De kunden råd om nästa steg i spårning och analys för att sedan leda kunden mo det
Leda och genomföra analys- och spåringsprojekt
Leverera och implementera tekniska spårningslösningar med hjälp av verktyg som Google Analytics och Google Tag Manager
Arrangera workshops för att samla in affärskrav för analysplattformen och översätta kundens affärsmål till en spårningsplan med mätbara KPI:er
Visualisera data genom att sätta upp instrumentpaneler och KPI-rapportering
Förbereda och presentera djupgående analysrapporter för kunder
VI SÖKER DIG SOM:
För att du ska trivas och lyckas i rollen söker vi dig som har,
Minst två års erfarenhet i en liknande roll där du använt Google Analytics och Google Tag Manager för webb och applikation
Erfarenhet av att sätta upp dashboard och rapportera in DataStudio, PowerBi, Tableau samt andra visualiseringsverktyg
Kunskap i databasspråk (T.ex. SQL) eller viljan att lära sig
Erfarenhet i Google Cloud plattform eller viljan att lära sig
Goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska då båda språken används internt i bolaget
För att trivas och lyckas i rollen på Rocket Revenue är det viktigt att du delar passionen för att ständigt vilja utvecklas och utmana dig själv, det är viktigt att du trivs i en dynamisk och föränderlig miljö, Rocket Revenues kultur är deras allt. Vi säker därför dig som är en lagspelare, som är självsäker men samtidigt ödmjuk. Utöver detta tror vi att du har en passion för data, djupt tekniskt kunnande, men framförallt är du en problemlösare med ett analytisk och nyfiket tänk.
OM KUNDFÖRETAGET:
Sedan 2015 har Rocket Revenue hjälpt företag att omvandla och optimera sin marknadsföring till en maskin för lönsam tillväxt. De använder kraften i Facebook, Google och andra digitala plattformar för att öka sin kunds tillväxt. De håller sina kunders händer när Apple uppdaterar iOS och när cookies dör. De trycker på knappen när det är dags att starta Black Week, och de berättar gärna för kunden när det är dags att sluta.
Förra året gav deras 200 kunder dem 8,4 av 10 i kundnöjdhet, några av de hade ökat sin tillväxt med 1000% tack vare strategin Rocket Revenue utvecklat, Rocket-strategin. Läs mer här.
OM ANSTÄLLNINGEN:
Detta är en direktrekrytering vilket innebär att du erbjuds en anställning direkt hos Rocket Revenue
ÖVRIG INFO:
Omfattning: Heltid
Start: Omgående/Enligt överenskommelse
Placering: Stockholm/Helsingborg (hybrid)
Rekryteringsansvarig: Elin Dahlqvist
Lön: Marknadsmässig
Ansök genom att klicka på länken nedan. Kom ihåg att vara snabb med din ansökan då vi gör löpande urval av kandidater och att annonsen kan stängs ner innan tjänsten är tillsatt om vi gått över till urvals och intervjufasen.
OM FRIDAY:
Genom att vara en partner både till våra kandidater och kunder strävar vi efter att hitta den bästa matchningen. Det gör vi genom att lära känna våra kunder och kandidater på riktigt! Vi ser självklart till att kunskaps- och erfarenhetskrav matchar, men framförallt lägger vi vikt vid samsyn kring värderingar och företagskultur som båda parter värdesätter.
Vår passion är att hjälpa människor till rätt roll, arbetsplats och sammanhang inom IT och teknik. Därför grundade vi Friday med ambition att hjälpa dig till jobbet som ger dig fredagskänslan – varje dag!
Vi riktar oss främst till dig som är i början av din karriär eller studerar vid högskola/universitet inom IT och Teknik.
Vår övertygelse är att människor uppnår sin fulla potential när man ser fram emot att gå till jobbet varje morgon. ”Friday – everyday”, hur låter det?

Title: Analytics Engineer
Description:
At Epidemic Sound we are reinventing the music industry. Our carefully curated catalog, with over 35,000 tracks, is tailored for storytellers, streaming services, and in-store soundtracks. Countless clients around the world, from broadcasters, production companies, DSPs, and YouTubers rely on our tracks to help them tell their stories. Epidemic Sound’s music is heard in hundreds of millions of online videos daily, across millions of playlist streams, and in thousands of in-store locations. Headquartered in Stockholm, we’re spread across offices in New York City, Los Angeles, Seoul, Hamburg, and Amsterdam. We’re growing fast, have lots of fun, and are taking the music industry with us.
We’re now looking for an Analytics Engineer to join our central Data engineering team, the team that is responsible for our Data Platform. You will play a vital role in ingesting data from our data lake into the data warehouse, where data will be transformed, scheduled, and made ready to be used for analytics & product development teams. You might come from a background where you have passion for Data Modeling or Data Engineering. Or you might have worked as a Data Scientist or Data Analyst and you’re curious and want to work more with Data Engineering.
In order for you to thrive in this role, we believe that you have one or more of the following:
Experience in SQL and Python
A strong interest and curiosity in data – you might have also worked with large-scale data warehouses like BigQuery or Snowflake, data modelling, and/or relational model design
Experience in any of the following tooling: Terraform, Snowplow, Apache Airflow, Fivetran, Looker, OpsGenie
Experience with cloud computing such as GCP or AWS
You definitely have the following:
A love for teamwork
A love for continuous improvement and learning
Follow best software engineering practices in your work
The ability to communicate in English with professional working proficiency
You value best practices but realize that all rules have exceptions
A passion for sharing your knowledge and teaching others what you know
Nice to have experience:
dbt
Previous experience working with or setting up ELT-like data pipelines

How you will make an impact
You would join Epidemic’s Data Engineering team, with a mission to provide the platform, tools, solutions, and data sets that enable the company to stay ever more data-informed. As an Analytics Engineer, you would play a key role in bridging Data Engineering and Data Analytics.
Our modern data stack runs on Google Cloud Platform and part of our solution stack includes BigQuery as a data warehouse, Google Cloud Composer (Airflow) for data pipeline orchestration, Dataflow jobs for data processing, and dbt for data transformation.

You can expect to:
Join an organization with passionate Data Scientists and Data Engineers at an early stage of the company's history. This is a chance to be part of building a data analytics platform that scales worldwide
Design, build and maintain the Epidemic data models
Drive data architecture matters, including following the data definition and data modeling principles across all parts of the business, and ensuring that everything from tracking to reporting cubes adheres to Epidemic’s best practices
Act as a stakeholder and partner with both engineering teams and analytics teams to deliver well-defined, tested, and high-quality data sets
Work with business stakeholders and design data models to quantitatively support everything from corporate strategy to user acquisition
Support and mentor analytics consumers on best software engineering practices
This role will include finding ways to share learnings across the organization. It could be via internal talks, writing internal blog posts, or any other way you may think of. You can also expect to learn a ton of new things, be it through hack-days, courses, conferences, or tech talks. We emphasize learning and we also expect you to share your knowledge with your colleagues.
We collaborate constantly and are big believers in teamwork and the value of practices like careful code reviews and pair (or mob) programming. On top of this, you can expect to have lots of fun and take pride in what you and all of Epidemic is doing.

Curious to learn more about who we are and what we do? Check out our brand new "About us" page https://www.epidemicsound.com/about-us/

We have lots of fun soundtracking the world and our annual Spring Bash is an event that captures this perfectly. Take a look at our most recent one, a virtual celebration!

Application
Do you want to be a part of our fantastic team? Please apply, in English, by clicking the link below.
We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business, and a better world. We value diversity and encourage everyone to come and soundtrack the world with us.

Title: Enterprise Architect - Information
Description:
Epiroc is currently seeking a driven Enterprise Architect - Information with a can-do attitude to be part of the Enterprise Architecture team. Do you have solid experience from this area? Then don’t hesitate to apply!

Your mission
As Enterprise Architect your mission will be:

Lead the global development of the requirements, principles and models for the future-state enterprise information architecture, as well as the documentation of the current-state information architecture.
Identify the gaps between the future-state and current-state information architecture and work with other enterprise architects to develop roadmaps for moving toward the future state.
Create and maintain IT strategies, based on business strategies within the organization’s goals and objectives.
Translate IT strategies into execution and evaluate and support solutions in line with the Epiroc IT target architecture.

Furthermore, you will collaborate with business and technology subject experts to transform business requirements into technological solutions. You will have the opportunity to review new IT solutions and projects to ensure they are compliant with Epiroc enterprise architecture principles, policies and guidelines. Monitor and analyze industry, technology and market trends to determine their potential impact for the organization will also be part of the work. You will build and maintain a holistic view of the organization’s strategy, capability, information and technology assets.

Your profile
To be able to contribute in the best way in this role you need a bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering or related field and have 10+ years in-depth experience in designing and implementing information solutions. It is important that you have a positive and open attitude with excellent communication skills. As a person you are organized, independent and your work is influenced by structure. We believe you are customer-oriented and service minded.

Experience in enterprise information architecture development is required. You should have a good understanding of information architecture frameworks, information models and trends. Additionally, you have knowledge of processes from several functional areas within a company.
Three to five years' experience as a data analyst is highly desirable. Hands-on experience implementing MDM, ML, BI or data warehouse solutions is preferred.

Since our corporate language is English it is required that your English skills (verbal and written) are fluent.

Location and travel
This position can be located in one of Epiroc IT Hub Locations: Perth (Australia), Prague (Czech Republic), Santiago (Chile), Nanjing (China), Bangalore (India), Boksburg (South Africa) Örebro or Stockholm (Sweden) or Garland (USA).

In case a candidate from a different country applies and is successful, international assignment terms and conditions may apply.

Life at Epiroc
By joining our team, you can expect an atmosphere of creativity, innovation, and workplace diversity. You will be a part of a group of skilled and helpful colleagues who live by our core values: Collaboration, Commitment, and Innovation. We work in a global environment with over 113 different nationalities!
In addition to the fact that we have a culture that is characterized by development combined with having a good balance between work and leisure, there are some things that makes us a little extra proud to work at Epiroc:

Global career opportunities
Epiroc University, for your own competence development
Community involvement
Benefits package, which amongst other things include flexible working hours and bonus.

A hybrid workplace
Life at Epiroc can include the possibility for a hybrid workplace. It is a way of working that offers flexibility and participation allowing for a better balance between work and private life, which also promotes well-being. The hybrid workplace is an opportunity if work allows, based on your role, responsibilities, and individual conditions.

Application and contact information
In this recruitment process, we review applications continuously. Welcome with your application as soon as possible by creating an account in our recruitment system. Last day to apply for this position is 2023-02-05.

For questions about the position please contact hiring manager: Andreas Bülow, Enterprise Architecture & IT PMO Manager, andreas.bulow@epiroc.com

For questions about the recruitment process or application please contact: Recruitment specialist Nesrin Kaddoura, Nesrin.kaddoura@epiroc.com

United. Inspired. Performance unites us, Innovation inspires us, and commitment drives us to keep moving forward.
In the 150 countries where you can find Epiroc, we encourage our employees to take ownership of their own development and careers with the support from their leaders.
We are committed to give you every opportunity to succeed in a culture of innovation, diversity and collaboration, combined with a caring atmosphere.
Diversity and sustainability are key to grow fresh and innovative ideas and solutions for our customers. Epiroc is a leading manufacturer for the mining and infrastructure industries. Learn more at www.epirocgroup.com

Title: Product Owner Data & Analytics for Telia Finance
Description:
Product Owner Data & Analytics
Do you want to bring new insight and solutions to help improve how Telia relies on data to make decisions and take actions?
My name is Marcus Söderberg and I am leading the Telia Finance Product Team. We are a team of 20 people responsible for Telia Finance financial product portfolio for B2B and B2C customers.
We are looking for our next team member to drive the Data and Business Analytics area within our B2B domain. In this role will work collaboratively with all business areas within Telia Finance to understand, challenge and document the requirements whilst leading the delivery of successful data driven initiatives. The position is based in Telia's HQ in Solna, Stockholm!
The role
As Product Owner Data & Analytics you will play a high-profile role in driving operational transformations within the analytics field. You will work on leading innovative transformation projects connected to the field of analytics and you will be a part of defining strategies, roadmaps, backlogs and execution plans to deliver business value to improve our stakeholders’ insights and operational efficiency.
In our Product Team you will work closely with other product owners, senior business stakeholders, developers and the IT departments in translating business needs into technical requirements for the product and development teams. In this role you will manage and drive your own activities, as part of a self-organizing team, you set the tone, build tasks, and determine what needs to get done.
Is this you?
We are looking for an experienced, business driven, and analytical team player that has the capability to analyse, drive insights and present business data in an easy and structured manner to different stakeholders.
Requirements
At least 3 years of experience in the analytics field, such as developer, data analyst, business analyst or product owner similar
Experience of working with complex project and different stakeholders
Experience in visualization tools such as Business Objects, Qlik Sense, Excel, or Power BI
An understanding of the fundamentals in data modelling and data warehousing
Good communication skills in Swedish and English
Experience of working with SAFe, Confluence, and Jira is considered a plus!
It’s more than just a job
At Telia Finance, we will give you the tools and support you need to grow both professionally and personally. We can offer you your next big opportunity in a creative, motivating, and welcoming company where everyone can be themselves with equal access to opportunities. In addition to an attractive and inclusive work environment, we also enable flexibility and offer a wide variety of employee benefits.
Interested?
If you find this interesting, don’t hesitate to apply for this job. If you have any questions or just want to hear more, feel free to connect with me on LinkedIn or contact our recruiter Ebba at ebba.pers@teliacompany.com or +46 76 496 44 06. We look forward to receiving your application!
Welcome to Telia Finance – Home to your next big opportunity!

Countless clients around the world, from broadcasters, production companies, DSPs, and YouTubers rely on our tracks to help them tell their stories. Title: Senior Controlling Analyst

The Sales Controller/BPO Salesforce-role is a key role in our Scandinavian Sales organization. As mentioned, you will also work closely with our Business/Data Analyst.
The role is a dual role, where we are looking for someone who can take on both Sales Controller-tasks and be the Business Process Owner for our Salesforce CRM-system as defined below.

Responsible for the financial sales reporting in

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.

For further information see www.babyshop.com

ABOUT THE POSITION

Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organization, where it acts as the foundation to our everyday work; whether it being more traditional reporting about what has happened, ad-hoc analysis to understand why that happened, or highly complex machine learning models to predict what will happen. We truly believe that one of the key factors of gaining a competitive advantage in a highly competitive market, is through the use of our data. As a Data Engineer, you will join the Data Team consisting of people with different expertise; Data Warehouse Developer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We use a combination of Fivetran and Apache Kafka to load data into our DWH Snowflake as well as DBT for transformation. Here you will get your hands dirty to understand and transform data using SQL for downstream tasks, ranging from analysis, to BI, to advanced ML use-cases. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO

Develop an understanding of source data as well as end-user needs, and use that to transform data into appropriate formats.
Collaborate with the other members of the Data Team to leverage data end-to-end, from discovering and connecting new data sources, load and transform, to be used for use-cases within BI/ML.
Use CI/CD best-practices together with version control to develop our dbt-workflow.
Use SQL best-practices to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, high performant code.
•

WHO YOU ARE

You have a passion for data & tech and appreciate a fast-paced entrepreneurial start-up vibe.
You have experience with relational databases and an excellent understanding of SQL.
You have experience in database design and modeling for data warehouse and business intelligence applications.
You are interested in keeping up to date with technological advancements within the data field, and are not afraid to try out new tech.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...

Have previous experience with dbt, and dbt Cloud.
Have previous experience with Snowflake.
Have previous experience with CI/CD and version control.
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Data Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.

Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28, however, applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!

Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: We are looking for a Project Manager!
Description:
We are looking for a Project Manager!
Do you want to help us and help those who are saving lives? How would it feel to actually make a difference and contribute to society differently than before? That is what you will be doing if you join our Order to Remittance- OTR Team. Every day, our solutions help Paramedics, Doctors, and other healthcare professionals to efficiently, and with high reliability provide the right care for sick or injured people. You will work together with talented individuals and with amazing products that literally save lives. Explore a career at Ortivus and join our team!
What will you do?
Ortivus is growing on the international arena and needs to strengthen our OTR team with an additional skilled Project Manager. In this role the Project Manager is responsible for the successful and timely software and service implementation, coordination, and management for international customer delivery projects. This position is responsible for defining, planning, and driving the team activities necessary to reach implementation objectives including the internal coordination of tasks with a project plan and ensuring that all tasks are completed on time and within budget. In this role, the project manager will work closely with all departments and customers serving as consultant, organizer, facilitator, planner, data analyst and problem solver as needed. Working independently and with minimal supervision, the project manager handles the implementation of medium to large scale customer implementations. The position will be based out of our Ortivus office in Danderyd, Stockholm, Sweden, and will involve travelling.
Who are we looking for?
To be successful as our new Project Manager you will have a minimum of 3 years of hands-on experience managing client facing projects and working in cross-functional teams, preferably, but not limited to the healthcare sector. You need to have the ability to be flexible, follow tight deadlines, independently organize, and prioritize work. Furthermore you have the ability and availability to travel to client sites for face-to-face meetings, interacting with all levels in an organization including executive management. If you have the ability to maintain composure, solve practical problems and successfully manage a variety of changing situations under stress and against tight deadlines this role is ideal for you. We also require the candidate to be fluent in English and Swedish at a professional level.
Apply Today!
If you would like to be part of a fantastic team, that is dedicated to saving lives, with Teamwork, Innovation and Customer Focus as our Values – please send in your application today through LinkedIn or to job@ortivus.com. Title: Biometria söker systemutvecklare till vårt team inom Business Intelligence
Description:
Biometria är en medlemsägd och central aktör inom svensk skogsnäring. Vi mäter det virke som flödar mellan skog och industri och som opartisk säkerställer vi att Sveriges skogsägare är trygga i sina virkesaffärer. Uppdraget är att stödja och utveckla virkeshandel, logistik och produktion på virkesmarknaden. Biometria erbjuder även tjänster för digitalisering och automatisering av virkesflödet och virkesaffärer, och vi har ett långsiktigt samarbete med forskningsinstitut och universitet. Genom vårt arbete verkar vi som ett informationsnav inom skogsnäringen och erbjuder en plattform med standardiserad och kvalitetssäkrad information som vi själva och andra aktörer kan bygga nya moderna tjänster på. Totalt är vi 850 anställda med verksamhet i hela Sverige, vårt huvudkontor ligger i Uppsala.
Vill du bidra till en digital revolution i skogens värdekedjor?
Inom Biometria driver vi den digitala utvecklingen för hela skogsnäringen. Vi skapar möjligheter inom digitalisering och innovation där vi testar ny teknologi. Biometria ligger i framkant avseende på både teknik och arbetssätt, bland annat genom att automatisera processen med hjälp av machine learning och AI.
Vi söker systemutvecklare till vårt team inom Business Intelligence (BI)
Vi letar efter dig som har ett passionerat intresse för ditt yrke, som gillar att lösa kluriga utmaningar och vill jobba med teknik som ligger i framkant. Har du en gedigen och mångårig erfarenhet eller är du nyutexaminerad och kunskapstörstig och vill lära dig? Vi värdesätter olikheterna i erfarenheter, kunskap och synsätt och ser det som viktiga byggklossar i en lärande organisation.
Biometria hanterar stora mängder data som ägs av våra kunder, i Biometrias data warehouse. I nuläget visualiserar vi datat till stor del i rapporter, som Biometrias kunder använder. Behovet av analyser kan komma att ändras med framtiden, där prognostisering blir alltmer viktigt för branschen.
Ditt ansvar och dina arbetsuppgifter
Du ingår i vårt utvecklingsteam där dina arbetsuppgifter är att utveckla de lösningar som Microsoft plattform Power BI möjliggör. Systemutvecklingen sker både i backend- och frontendmiljö och vi arbetar i en microservices-arkitektur i Azure. Vi går mot att bli en DevOps-organisation där teamen tar ett helhetsansvar över våra produkter.
I backend jobbar vi med ett antal ramverk och programspråk såsom Azure SQL server, Blobstorage, .NET Core, Azure Keyvault, Azure Functions, BIML (Business Intelligence Markup Language). Datat struktureras med datamodellen data vault i olika relationsdatabaser och laddar tabulärer för vidare bearbetning och visualisering i frontend.
I frontend jobbar vi med ett antal ramverk och programspråk såsom Azure SQL server, SSAS (SQL Server Analysis Services), tabulärmodeller, DAX, SSIS (SQL Server Integration Services), External tables, Data Factory, Azure Analytics, BIML, Star Schema (fakta och dimensionstabeller), Azure AD, Power BI. Dataskiss skapas i ett Star Schema och utifrån strukturerat data i tabulärer skapas en eller flera rapporter, eller andra typer av analyser i Power BI.
Som systemutvecklare har du ansvar för att stötta teamet i tekniska problemlösningar med utgångspunkt från slutanvändarens behov. Du har täta kontakter med andra systemutvecklare, användbarhetsexperter, IT-arkitekter, testare, verksamhetsutvecklare samt produktägare
Vem är du?
Du gillar statistik och matematik, har högskoleutbildning eller relevant IT-utbildning inom området, i rollerna Data engineer, Data analyst eller Data scientist. Du är orädd, nyfiken och gillar utmaningar. Du trivs med att vara del av ett team och har lätt för att samarbeta, men är också självgående och drivande inom ditt område. Du gillar att jobba i ett öppet samarbetsklimat i en grupp som har ett helhetsansvar för de produkter som finns inom produktområdet. Du gillar att hantera och strukturera stora datamängder samt modellera och ta fram bra analysverktyg för kunden.
Vi ser gärna att du kan tänka utanför ramarna och vill ligga i framkant med de nyaste teknikerna inom Microsoft Power BI och vill utvecklas i takt med nya tekniksprång.
Vårt erbjudande
Våra värderingar är ledord för vårt förhållningssätt och våra värdeord är pålitliga, opartiska, engagerade och tillsammans. Alla ska ha utrymme för att kunna utföra sitt uppdrag, att våga testa och även ta hjälp av varandra för att lyckas. Det ska kännas tryggt och roligt att komma till jobbet. Vi stöttar varandra och ser varandra som kollegor och medmänniskor.
Vi erbjuder dig ett självständigt arbete med möjlighet att arbeta på distans.
Vi erbjuder också privat sjukvårdsförsäkring samt att vi har flera fritidsboenden att låna/hyra och självklart erbjuder vi våra anställda friskvårdsbidrag.
Biometria verkar för att skapa en attraktiv arbetsplats med öppenhet och ett tillåtande klimat. Varje medarbetares individuella förutsättningar och kompetens tas tillvara – det är bra att vi är olika!
Vid en anställning skapar vi en plan för dig för att du ska få en så bra introduktion som möjligt till vår tekniska plattform och organisation.
Din ansökan
Vänligen skicka in din ansökan genom länken nedan. Din ansökan skall innehålla en presentation av dig själv och vad som lockar med tjänsten samt en meritförteckning/CV.
Information om anställningen
Löne- och anställningsvillkor: Enligt gällande kollektivavtal
Tillträde: Enligt överenskommelse
Anställningsform: Tillsvidare
Anställningens omfattning: Heltid
Upplysningar om anställningen lämnas av: Produktområdeschef för Produktion och BI, Ted Danielsson, 010-228 50 47
Fackliga representanter: Jens Nordenberg, Akademikerföreningen 010-228 51 16 och Marie Söder, Unionen 010-228 5139
Välkommen att skicka in din ansökan senast den 2023-02-20
Vi har gjort vårt medieval för rekrytering och undanber oss erbjudanden om rekryterings- och annonseringshjälp.
Genom din ansökan samtycker du till att Biometria får nyttja dina personuppgifter i syfte att genomföra rekryteringsarbete kopplat till denna tjänst i enlighet med Dataskyddsförordningen GDPR. Vänligen läs mer på Integritetsskyddsmyndigheten. (imy.se)

Title: LFV söker Projektledare
Description:
Avdelningen System och Utveckling (SoU) bedriver kommunikations-, navigations- och övervakningstjänster. Avdelningen ansvarar dessutom för LFVs administrativa informationsteknologi, utvecklingsverksamhet samt system-planering och anskaffning. Vidare ansvarar avdelningen för LFVs tekniska utrustningar för flygtrafikledningstjänst, flygbriefingtjänst och flygvädertjänst. Totalt är vi ca 160 anställda på SoU.

Projektkontoret består idag av två grupper med projektledare, programledare samt portföljledare och en data analyst. Projektkontorets uppdrag och ansvarsområde är att tillsätta projektledare till våra projekt och program, utveckla och effektivisera projektmetodik och -processer. Enheten är en del av SoU och vi är idag ca 30 medarbetare, både anställda och konsulter. Inom enheten hanterar vi idag flertalet projekt, t.ex inom it- och cyberområdet, radio/COM och remote tower.

Många av våra framtida projekt är utifrån vårt utökade uppdrag att tillhandahålla en säker, effektiv och miljöanpassad flygtrafiktjänst för civil och militär luftfart oberoende av beredskapsnivå. Här hittar mer information om oss - Om LFV

Vi står inför en spännande framtid och söker nu flera projektledare.

Din roll
Som projektledare arbetar du aktivt med att planera, leda och styra tilldelade projekt samt inom dessa projekt skapa ett kreativt arbetsklimat som stimulerar nytänkande. Utöver detta ingår att aktivt medverka till Projekt och Verksamhetsutvecklings funktion inom LFV vilket inkluderar att säkerställa att projekten genomförs enligt rådande projektmodell.

Exempel på arbetsuppgifter:
Projektplanering inklusive resursestimat, risk- och intressentanalys
Säkerställa leverans av uppdragens nytta
Upphandling av tekniskt avancerade system
Ledning och styrning av tvärfunktionella team
Implementering av förändring
Din Profil

Civilingenjörsutbildning eller har motsvarande arbetslivserfarenhet som vi bedömer som likvärdig.
Goda kunskaper i projektledning.
Erfarenhet av att leda och styra tvärfunktionella team.
Erfarenhet av forsknings- leverans- och/eller utvecklingsprojekt.
Erfarenhet av att leda IT- och IT-infrastrukturprojekt.
Grundläggande kunskap inom företagsekonomi.
Mycket goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska i tal och skrift.
Rollen som projektledare kräver att du är initiativtagande och mål- och resultatorienterad. Du är lösningsinriktad och du driver självständigt dina processer vidare. Du har god analytisk förmåga, ser helhetsperspektiv och kan hantera flera frågor parallellt. Du är kommunikativ och kan hantera intressenter på olika nivåer och befattningar.

Vi kommer att lägga stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper.

Anställning och förmåner
Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning på någon av våra placeringsorter (Norrköping-huvudkontor eller Malmö-Sturup). Innan anställning genomför LFV en säkerhetsprövning som bland annat innefattar registerkontroll, säkerhetsintervju och drogtest. Denna tjänst kräver svenskt medborgarskap.

LFV har goda anställningsvillkor och ett brett utbud av förmåner som bland annat innefattar en privat sjukvårdsförsäkring och goda pensionsvillkor.

Urval, personlighetstester och intervjuer till tjänsten kommer att ske löpande under ansökningstiden.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.

For further information see www.babyshop.com

ABOUT THE POSITION

Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO

Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE

You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...

Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE

The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.

Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!

Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Data Officer | Financial Data | Nordic Leader
Description:
Data Officer | Financial Data | Nordic Leader
NFI - 22.11.2022 AVW_1669194413
This company aims to help their customers make informed decisions on their financial and insurance matters. Here they're looking to add a Data Officer to their ranks to help streamline this process within their Wealth Management sector.

Well-established within their market this organisation is focused on ensuring their insights are data-driven to ensure that only the most relevant information is gathered and thus the best advice on finance, insurance and wealth management can be given.

Wealth Management is a fairly young company but they have been rapidly growing over the last few years creating the demand for the tech and data teams to similarly match this growth. Here you will be at the core for helping the business become more data-driven and as such have a fantastic opportunity to be a crucial part of the business and have a big impact in its success.

If you're passionate about data and have an interest within the financial market then this is the opportunity for you to have an impact in an already dominating business.

Title: App Developer
Description:
Are you ready to redefine the financial industry? Are you looking to leave an impact on the financial lives (and futures) of hundreds of thousands of families across the Nordics? Does a serious technical challenge make your heart beat faster? Do you give energy to those who work with you and are you looking for an energy boosting work environment? Then Nordnet is the place for you!
For us Transparent Banking is not just a slogan!
In brief
Nordnet’s mobile app team is a cross functional and autonomous team, consisting of developers, UX designers, a data analyst, a Product Owner, and an Engineering Manager. The Nordnet app was first released in 2018 – developed from scratch to replace the old mobile app. The team keeps a very high delivery cadence, releasing a new app version to our customers every week!
This is part of the role
As a mobile app developer, you will build on one of the biggest pillars in the financial market. The app has hundreds of thousands of active users and is our most visited channel. As an app developer you will use modern technologies (e.g. React Native, Redux) that handle everything from executing real-time trades, push notifications, streaming real time prices, to advanced financial graphs at the fingertips of users. You will work in a highly collaborative environment (we usually mob or pair program) and you will contribute to what direction the product is going to take.
This is who you are
To succeed in this role, we believe that you take great pride in your work and continuously work on becoming a better developer and a great communicator. Discussing ideas and concepts and learning from your peers is something you believe is important to build great products. You have previously worked with agile methodologies (Scrum, Kanban) with focus on testing and you have MSc certification or similar within Computer Science.
As a developer, you:
Are highly communicative, transparent and a good listener
Let code win arguments (ego doesn’t excite you)
Are eager to learn and grow
Are humble
Take pride in delivering
Are solution oriented and care deeply about the user experience
Care about code quality, testing and automation of the finished product.
Preferred experience:
React Native
RESTful APIs
JavaScript (ES6)
Mobile app development
We offer
Nordnet started from a passionate belief that changing the hierarchic financial world was possible. We became part of redefining the industry when we gave the customers power over their own savings. You will become part of a journey that has only yet started towards the vision of making our customers the best investors they can be. To be leading in IT is pivotal for that journey and you will work with colleagues who have a great passion for that goal.
We are 600 employees in Stockholm, Oslo, Helsinki and Copenhagen. We cooperate, exchange ideas and use our core competencies in order to continuously improve the way we meet our customers. Open communication, creativity and engagement are important parts of our everyday life at the office.
Visit us on: www.nordnetab.com, www.nordnet.se, www.nordnet.no, www.nordnet.dk_ and _www.nordnet.fi.
Application
Please apply today by using the button below – we will start interviewing immediately. Please note that we do only accept applications through our recruitment system, hence no email applications will be considered.
If you have questions, please contact Head of Talent Acquisition Heidi Ershult, heidi.ershult@nordnet.se
We want to inform you that Nordnet conduct credit and background checks on the final candidate.
We look forward to receiving your application!
Job Type: Full-time

Title: BI-kompetens till Sogeti Luleå
Description:
Ansök nu
Data & AI är ett fokuserat satsningsområde som genomsyrar Sogeti lokalt, nationellt och globalt. Följ med oss på en spännande resa!
Vi söker dig som vill jobba med ny teknik inom området för BI, data management med roller som BI-utvecklare, Data Engineer, Data Scientist och Data Analyst!
Data & AI handlar för oss främst om att skapa möjligheter för våra kunder att fatta bättre affärsbeslut, att förstå kundernas verksamhet samt att kunna fokusera på kundnytta. Vi arbetar brett inom fältet och älskar nya tekniker; med allt från nyutveckling i framkant till förvaltning och med tekniker som till exempel Azure Data Faktory, Azure Data Lake, Databricks, Machine Learning och Power BI. Vårt främsta fokus är verktyg inom Microsoft BI-sviten men teknik är alltid underordnat kundnytta, vi gör det som är bäst för våra kunder!
Inom Sogeti finns det många hjälpsamma och glada kollegor med stor erfarenhet inom området. Vi prioriterar en balans mellan arbete och fritid högt och har en familjär arbetskultur. Det finns även ett brett nätverk inom hela Sogeti som hjälper dig att bredda och spetsa dina kunskaper.
Som BI-utvecklare på Sogeti Luleå kommer du att hjälpa våra kunder både genom strategiska och operativa förbättringar, få spännande inblick i en rad olika verksamheter och utveckla din egen kompetens!
Vem söker vi?
Du trivs i rollen som konsult i framkant, med möjlighet att växa och få ett omväxlande arbete. Vi tror att du är fokuserad, lösningsorienterad, nyfiken, analytisk och tekniskt skicklig. Du kan arbeta självgående och du brinner för ditt område och vill ha möjligheter att vidareutvecklas.

Vi tror att du kanske har erfarenhet av eller vill jobba med nya tekniker inom:
Azure, Cloud
Modern data plattform
Data/ data management
Azure Data Faktory/Data Lake och Databricks
Vi tror att du har:
Minst 3 års dokumenterad erfarenhet inom BI
Relevant teknisk högskoleutbildning
Erfarenhet av Power BI
Kunskaper om datalager, SSIS, SSRS, SSAS
Erfarenhet av SQL Server
Du talar och skriver flytande svenska och uttrycker dig väl i tal och skrift på engelska.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Stadium utökar sitt Data & Analytics team och letar efter en Data Scientist.
Är du vår nästa stjärnspelare?
Har du ett stort intresse för avancerad analys och AI och tycker att retail och Stadium verkar spännande? Vill du vara en del av ett innovativt team och kunna bidra till att utveckla Stadiums strategiska position? Då är du personen vi letar efter.
Vad innebär det att vara Data Scientist?
Som Data Scientist på Stadium kommer du att ansvara för att genomföra analyser, skapa insikter och förmedla vidare dessa till organisationen. Du kommer att designa, utveckla och utvärdera avancerade prediktiva modeller. Du är en affärsdriven person som får energi av att dra slutsatser ur stora datamängder och gillar att jobba nära verksamheten. Du har med fördel erfarenhet från retail eller andra större bolag.
Rollen innebär att du arbetar som informations- och insiktspecialist mot hela organisationen. Du kommer att använda Machine Learning och statistiska metoder för att ta fram skalbara lösningar på problem.
Förutom ovanstående nämnda uppgifter kommer ditt övergripande ansvar innebära att:
Vara en nyckelperson i flertalet projekt och crossfunktionella team.
Skapa dashboards, segmenteringar och rapporteringslösningar som på ett effektivt sätt kan kommuniceras till verksamheten.
Identifiera, analysera och tolka trender/mönster i komplexa datamängder.
Tillämpa och utveckla prediktiva modeller.

Vem är du?
För att lyckas i rollen är du en social person med en positiv inställning och ett bra driv. Det är viktigt att du är en lagspelare och tror på samarbete, men samtidigt känner dig trygg med att jobba självständigt. Vi ser gärna att du har ett stort kundfokus och alltid strävar efter att leverera hög kvalitet. Tjänsten kräver att du behärskar engelska och svenska i både tal och skrift.
Du har relevant akademisk utbildning inom exempelvis matematik, statistik eller liknande.
Du har bra förståelse för data science och kunskaper om tillämpning av statistiska metoder.
Du har erfarenhet av analysverktyg som R/Python och SQL.
Du är insiktsdriven och kundorienterad.
Rollen innebär en unik möjlighet till att kombinera din analytiska sida med ditt kommersiella driv. Du kommer att bli en del av ett kvalificerat analysteam med målet att vidareutveckla organisationen genom insikter och data science.
Varaktighet/arbetstid
Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning med tillträde enligt överenskommelse. Provanställning tillämpas.
Ansökan
Ansökan Som en del i rekryteringsprocessen kommer du att få en inbjudan till din e-mail till att besvara ett personlighetstest och ett kapacitetstest. Det tar ca 30 minuter att besvara testen.
Eftersom vi alltid vill vara på tårna och göra saker så enkelt som möjligt är det inte säkert att vi väntar till sista ansökningsdag innan vi går vidare i rekryteringsprocessen. Så vänta inte med din ansökan utan sök redan idag!
Välkommen med din ansökan. Come join the movement!

Vi har riktigt bra förmåner
En arbetsplats där alla är välkomna
Utbildning och utveckling
Gemenskap och glädje
Rättvis och marknadsmässig lön
Träningsbidrag
Personalrabatt

Title: Summer Internship, Data Science | Platform Mission (EMEA)
Description:
Students
The Platform team creates the technology that enables Spotify to learn quickly and scale easily, enabling rapid growth in our users and our business around the globe. Spanning many fields, we work to make the business work; creating the frameworks, capabilities and tools needed to welcome a billion customers. Join us and help to amplify productivity, quality and innovation across Spotify.
Location
Stockholm or Remote EMEA
Job type
Internship
We are looking for Data Scientist Interns to Join The Band and help drive a data-first culture across Spotify, with a focus on internal productivity. You will analyze internal networks within the Spotify organization to better understand how people at Spotify communicate and collaborate with each other.
What you'll do
Be a valued member of an autonomous, multi-functional agile team focusing on understanding and enabling developers’ productivity.
Collaborate with other data scientists, engineers, product managers, designers and user researchers to tackle exciting and challenging problems.
Be a member of the Spotify-wide data-science community.
Perform analyses on internal datasets to extract practical insights that will help drive decisions across the business.
Build dashboards and recurring reporting results, empowering creative growth and business decisions.
Communicate data-driven insights and recommendations to key collaborators.
Who you are
You are pursuing a Bachelor’s, Master’s degree, or bootcamp certification in Science, Computer Science, Statistics, Economics, Mathematics, or a similar quantitative subject area
You have a graduation date of 2023 or 2024.
You currently have valid work authorization to work in the country in which this role is based that will extend from June to August 2023.
You harbor a passion for numbers and the use of data to make decisions.
You have the technical competence to perform more analytics in one or more of the following areas:
Coding skills (such as Python or R).
Analytics tools experience (such as Pandas, SQL, or Tableau).
Experience performing data analysis.
Where you'll be
We are a distributed workforce enabling our band members to find a work mode that is best for them!
Where in the world? For this role, it can be within the EMEA region in which we have a work location.
Prefer an office to work from instead? Not a problem! We have plenty of options for your working preferences. Find more information about our Work From Anywhere options here.
Working hours? We operate within the Central European time zone for collaboration.
Our global benefits
Extensive learning opportunities, through our dedicated team, GreenHouse.
All The Feels, our employee assistance program and self-care hub.
Social events, everything from fikas and team outings to concerts, panels and talks.
Flexible public holidays, swap days off according to your values and beliefs.
Spotify Premium Account, listen without limits with a free employee account.
Swag, a Spotify welcome kit and official merch you can’t get anywhere else.
Learn about life at Spotify
Our paid summer internships last for 10-13 weeks and start at the beginning of June. The last day to apply is February 7th, 2023 at 10 AM CET.

Spotify is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome at Spotify for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what’s playing in your headphones. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all thrive, contribute, and be forward-thinking! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our differences that we will find the power to keep revolutionizing the way the world listens.

Spotify transformed music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the chance to enjoy and be passionate about these creators. Everything we do is driven by our love for music and podcasting. Today, we are the world’s most popular audio streaming subscription service.

Title: Data Scientist - Stockholm, Solna
Description:
Are you passionate about machine learning and data analysis? Do you want to work in an international organization where your techniques will have a great impact on the business and customers? We are looking for a Data Scientist for the Process & System Development team who will be based in Solna.

At Arla, we strive to unlock the highest potential in each other while working together to create a sustainable future of dairy. We call it Stronger People Stronger Planet and it is deeply anchored in our organisation and founded on our commitment to respecting human rights, increasing access to healthy dairy nutrition, inspiring good food habits, and improving the environment for future generations. In order to succeed we need to hire people with a sustainable mindset.

About the job
As a Data Scientist at Arla you will be part of the Process & System Development team where you work together to develop processes and systems and identify new development areas with the focus on digital services. This can be services that supports our customers with information or services about purchases and deliveries of our products.

You will be a part of our function who works with Big Data, BI and AI with focus on analysis and predictive analysis. The role include a responsibility to identify and implement new technology to further develop our digital services and also analys and visualise data insights. You will be a part of the whole process, from the first idea to finished product.

The role as Data Scientist also include:
Collaborating with colleagues, customers and suppliers to gain knowledge about business issues
Analys data to identify new development areas and new solutions
Design and develop models with machine learning and optimizing techniques
Exchange knowledge with different markets within Arla through our Globala Data Science Community

Who are you?
We are looking for someone who is driven and wants to start their working career at Arla, we believe that you are newly graduated from the univeristy or have previous experience within Data Science. You have programming skills and enjoy analysing Big Data, you would also like to learn more about data bases and their structure. It is important that you are structured and methodical, and can explain complicated technical things in a pedagogical way in the dialogue with others.

In order to be successful in this role we believe that you have:
Experience of a tool box for machine learning/deep learning
Experience of programming, Python and/or R
The ability to identify solutions through data analysis
The ability to design and develop models with machine learning and optimizing techniques
An analytical ability to understand business issues
Fluent in English, both written and oral

It is meritorious if you have:
Experience in presentation tools such as Power BI, Dundas BI or Tableau
Technical knowledge about data bases and cloud technology such as Databricks or Azure
An interest in modelling and data pipelines
Previously worked with agile development techniques
Knowledge in Swedish writing/speaking

What do we offer?
We’re committed to professional development and promoting from within. Our positive and collaborative culture will bring out the best in you. And you’ll join a market leader who produces nutritious household favorite brands in a way that make things better for our customers, the farmers who own us, and the whole world.

Create the future – Grow with Arla

Application and contact
Please apply as soon as possible but no later than 2023.02.11. We process applications on a continuous basis and close the job opening once the right candidate has been found. Finding the right candidate is of high importance and for this, we can be flexible on the starting date. For additional information, please contact Thomas Peterson, Team Manager, arthpet@arlafoods.com.

At Arla Foods we want to create the conditions for our colleagues to have a sustainable work life by offering flexibility and the opportunity to work in the office, which is seen as the first choice, and remotely; based on the needs of the business and the employees. We call it the “Power of the Mix”.

Arla Foods is bound by collective agreements. At Arla we always make sure to offer good and competitive working conditions.

We have a purpose for Good
At Arla, we strive to unlock the highest potential in each other while working together to create a sustainable future of dairy. We call it Stronger People Stronger Planet and it is deeply anchored in our organisation and founded on our commitment to respecting human rights, increasing access to healthy dairy nutrition, inspiring good food habits, and improving the environment for future generations. In order to succeed we need to hire people with a sustainable mindset. Could this be you?

BEWARE! RECRUITMENT FRAUD
It has come to our attention that there are a number of fraudulent emails and fake recruitment campaigns on the internet from people purporting to work for Arla Foods. Learn more via this link.

Kodiak Hub is a growth venture offering SaaS solutions engineered to revolutionize Supplier Relationship Management (SRM).
