Title: Data Scientist
Description:
At Tetra Pak we commit to making food safe and available, everywhere; and we protect what's good – protecting food, protecting people, and protecting the planet. By doing so we touch millions of people's lives every day. And we need people like you to make it happen.
Job Summary
We are looking for a Data Scientist, who will belong to the Tetra Pak´s Decision Science Team. You will participate in various projects, influence business decisions, and drive digital transformation at one of the largest consumer packaging companies in the world.

This position will be placed in Lund, Sweden.
What you will do
Participate in data science projects, be hands-on and build statistical models and determine optimal modeling approach for each business scenario
Oversee junior data scientists
Development, test, implement and deployment of data science solutions to solve various business issues.
Work closely with Sr. Data Scientists, and Data Scientist Managers, Business stakeholders and subject matter experts to review expected outputs and applicability to business challenge.
Identify and take part in operationalization of valuable insights from the data into business and digital applications.
Partner with internal/external stakeholders, product owners and team members and drive product development plans
Drive methodological innovations into data science and digital products in the different functional areas such as services, product development, supply chain, operations optimization, and similar domains
We believe you have
In this role as Data Scientist, you need to have with a good balance in these three different profiles:

Technical:
Strong coding skills in Python. Ability to write efficient code for deployment.
Experience developing deployment ready code with focus on robustness and efficient deployment.
Experience with R, C, Java or functional programming are meriting.
Experience building optimization automation for food processing industry.
Experience in neural network techniques for time series and image analysis and natural language processing are meriting.


Statistics & Mathematics: Knowledge of quantitative methods is important. From statistical inference to predictive and prescriptive modelling together with optimization skills. You have a strong algorithmic thinking and independent research ability.
Proven skills in multi-objective optimization applied to operations.
Experience with evolutionary computing for optimization.
Experience with fuzzy logic for modelling of uncertainty.
Analyse data with statistical rigor. Ensure accurate interpretation by combining business acumen with detailed data knowledge and statistical expertise. Ability for summarizing and explaining results focusing on the important information.
Build statistical models to uncover insights or effect changes and provides solutions to business problems.
Knowledge about common statistical models and machine learning models, i.e. understands what is going on “underneath the hood


Functional: Good understanding of operational processes, KPI’s and decision supporting systems. Mainly in areas like production, quality, maintenance, logistics and after-sales process (warranty). Complementary revenue management for pricing and marketing (customer insights).
Translate analytic insights into concrete, actionable recommendations for business or product improvement, and communicate these findings.
Drive efforts to enable independent interpretation of results through education, improved tools, and data visualization.
We Offer You
A variety of exciting challenges with ample opportunities for development and training in a truly global landscape
A culture that pioneers a spirit of innovation where our industry experts drive visible results
An equal opportunity employment experience that values diversity and inclusion
Market competitive compensation and benefits with flexible working arrangements

Apply Now
If you are inspired to be part of our promise to protect what’s good; for food, people, and the planet, apply through our careers page at https://jobs.tetrapak.com/.


This job posting expires on 2023-02-05
To know more about the position contact Pedro Corral at +46 46 36 1247
Questions about your application contact Susanne Stålring at +46 46 36 3919
For trade union information contact Sveriges Ingenjörer Lars Haraldsson at +46 46 36 2533 and Unionen Lisbeth Larsson at +46 46 36 2320

Title: Chief Data Scientist
Description:
Datatera bridges the gap between healthcare and technology by providing HealthTech companies access to high-quality, real-world Health data which enables them to create accurate AI models that will elevate healthcare innovation and increase value for patients.

We are searching for someone who is passionate about Health Data and willing to take the role of Chief Data Scientist to help us with building our AI Module and being the key person in our Data Science strategy and working closely with the CTO.

This role requires;

Having at least 5+ years of experience with Data Science and AI
Having an entrepreneurial/creative mind and belief in the company's vision
Having prior Health Data experience is definitely a big plus
Having a good work ethic & good communication skills are equally important
Looking forward to receiving your application.

Title: Business Developer / BDR (Data Science startup)
Description:
About Forloop:
Forloop is on the mission to enable data teams to navigate the fast and unpredictable world that we live in today - by levering External Data. Forloop enables data teams to leverage external data (data outside the company), to have an information advantage on their markets. Used today in Real Estate (to price properties), Logistics (capacity planning) and Retail (adapt to trends).

Forloop was founded in 2021, and is based Stockholm and Prague with a remote-friendly culture. Backed by renowned investors including APX, Rockstart Ventures and Depo Ventures and angels.

With fresh funding, we are now looking to expand our team across product and sales. Here you will work with an ambitiös team with backgrounds in data, machine-learning and startups. And now, you can be part of the journey!

About the role:
You will play an important role in driving new business leads and working closely with the founders to grow the company. We are looking for a driven, curious, solution-oriented sales enthusiast to grow our customer base.

What you will do:
You will work closely with founders through the whole sales cycle. Focus on net-new accounts.
Define and refine our ideal outbound prospects and how to reach them, and learning more about our sales process along the way.
Meaning: 1) finding and reach out to relevant leads 2) do solution-oriented meetings to understand customer requirements 3) drive the deal forward 4) close
Creating and testing new pipeline generation opportunities and hypotheses
Create the playbooks for outbound sales work to create the foundation for the Business Developers and SDRs who will follow in your footsteps
Use CRM, Linkedin, email and phone as your tools.
What we look for:
Your background may be unconventional; as long as you have the essential qualifications, we encourage you to apply. While having "bonus" qualifications makes for a strong candidate, Forloop values diverse experiences.

Quick learner and interested in pursuing a career in data- and technology solutions.
Likes to be the bridge between data, infrastructure and business value and be able to communicate to these different people.
An interest to learn about data and ML tooling, workflows, and industry trends.
Driven and competitive: Possess a strong desire to be successful.
Previous experience either as an SDR/BDR, or in a closing role
Experience from sales in SaaS or tech is a plus.
Benefits:
Have an important role and influence the direction of the company.
Personal and career development to a leadership role, with a talented and ambitious team, in a dynamic and fast-growing market.
Access to be forefront of ML tooling, and industry trends. Skills and knowledge that can and will be important for future leaders as more and more companies will make use of data.
Stock options programme is possible.
Work with us from Prague, Stockholm, or from anywhere.
Do you want to be a part of our journey? Please apply by clicking the link below!

We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business and a better world .

Title: R&D Data Sciences & AI Graduate Programme - Sweden
Description:
R&D Data Sciences & AI Graduate Programme – Sweden
Locations: Gothenburg (Sweden)
Fuel your curiosity, feel valued and follow the science
If you have a quantitative science focused bachelor’s or master’s degree and a desire to explore and develop your skills in data science and artificial intelligence within a global biopharmaceutical organisation, our R&D Data Science & AI Graduate Programme could be the perfect start to your career. You’ll gain invaluable insight, exposure and opportunities across our diverse, Research and Development organisation. We’ll accelerate your learning and help you achieve your potential.
About AstraZeneca
AstraZeneca is a global, science-led, patient-focused biopharmaceutical company that focuses on the discovery, development and commercialisation of prescription medicines for some of the world’s most serious diseases.
Embrace the novel opportunity to work at a business that puts patients first. Working with data and an agile mindset in our constantly changing business, we help uncover solutions that power the business to better harness the science and get it to market. It means we play our part in reaching patients in need and influencing outcomes.
What does the programme involve?
Starting in September 2023, the programme lasts two years, consisting of three individual eight month placements. Each placement will provide you with fantastic insights and experience in our use of machine learning, AI and data science to advance drug discovery and development.
The programme’s variety and flexibility provides you with opportunities to apply machine learning, AI, and data science techniques to help push our scientists push the boundaries of science to develop life changing medicines for patients worldwide. You could be contributing to detecting safety risks, designing novel molecules, optimising clinical trial design and processes, or developing new models for use in high profile drug discovery and development projects. As well as helping you broaden your industry and technical knowledge, we’ll help you develop professional skills required to fulfill your career potential.
You will gain an invaluable blend of on-the-job experience and training. You’ll enjoy guidance and advice from a huge support network, including a mentor and dedicated programme management team. We’ll also encourage you to identify and build collaborative relationships with specialists and leaders across our organisation, and our external networks including leading academic and biotech research institutions.
Together, we’ll help accelerate your development and knowledge!
Essential requirements
Highly numerate with a strong quantitative science (e.g. Maths, Physics, Statistics or Computer Science) focused Bachelors or Masters level qualification gained in 2022 or due to be completed by September 2023
Hands-on experience in Data Science, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Statistics, Computational Biology, Computational Chemistry, Bioinformatics or Cheminformatics
Deep understanding of a few key machine learning or statistical models
Considerable experience in Python or experience with multiple data-centric programming languages enabling Big data analysis
Innovative thinking, with enthusiasm, energy and drive
Open-minded, and ready to embrace new ideas and different perspectives
Strong critical thinking, planning, organisational and time management skills
Ability to work as part of a collaborative team
Able to start employment in September 2023
Together, we push the boundaries of science to deliver life-changing medicines to patients around the world!
Where can I find out more?
Early careers at AstraZeneca
Our Social Media
Follow AstraZeneca on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/1603/
Follow AstraZeneca on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/astrazenecacareers/
Follow AstraZeneca on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/astrazeneca_careers/?hl=en
What next?
After you submit your application, you will be asked to complete an online assessment (SHL). If shortlisted, you will then be invited to a full day virtual assessment day.
Our virtual assessment days will be held week commencing 17th April 2023
Advert Opens 06 December 2022
Advert closes 19 February 2023

Title: Data Scientist som vill skapa framtida historia
Description:
Hej!

Vilken framtida historia vill du skapa?
Vi på Artificial Collective
vill skapa framtida historia med AI och förbättra vardagen för miljarder människor, varelser och vår planet inom det kommande decenniet!

Det är vår vision, och den är stor!

Men vi är på god väg då vi idag samarbetar med några av Nordens mest spännande företag där vi tillsammans med de mest passionerade inom AI/Data, inspirerar vi varandra varje dag och riktar vår samlade kunskap mot att skapa de bästa AI-lösningarna som bidrar med en större nytta.
Bli en del av teamet ‍‍
som idag består av seniora konsulter inom Data Science och Machine Learning. För att fortsätta arbeta med de mest spännande projekten, söker vi just nu efter vår nästa kollega inom Data Science.

Som anställd eller egen konsult hos Artificial Collective får du möjligheten att arbeta med just det ditt hjärta bultar extra för. Både i individuella och i teamprojekt.

Du själv bestämmer över din tid, ersättning, vad du vill arbeta med och i vilken riktning du vill utvecklas. Istället för en gammeldags hierarki med konsultchefer, får du som en del av Artificial Collective, en dedikerad agent som tillsammans med dig ser till att du kommer dit! Exempelvis genom utbildning, inspiration eller med hjälp av mentorskap från en expert inom önskat område.

Vi söker inte enbart efter någon som har rätt teknisk bakgrund, utan någon som vill vara med och fortsätta forma Artificial Collective till det bästa möjliga, med och för oss alla.


Vi tror att du brinner för

Använda olika metoder för att hantera data, saknad data, obalanserad data, felaktig data, extremvärden osv.
Förstå, assistera och förbättra den befintliga processen för att underhålla och utöka data.
Formulera och strukturera problem för att hitta och kommunicera en väg framåt.
Analysera och visualisera komplexa data för att hitta nya mönster och insikter som kommer förbättra verksamheten och upplevelsen.
Bygga och producera AI-lösningar med olika ML-tekniker.
Programmera i lämpligt språk så som Python och SQL.

Vårt löfte
är att ge dig vad du behöver för att du ska kunna lägga mer tid på det som ditt hjärta bultar extra för!
Vi tror på frihet och att det skapar välmående vilket vi ser som avgörande för passion samt geniala idéer.
Vi tror på passion och att det är viktigt för glädje och fortsatt lärande. Vi vill frigöra din passion.
‍‍ Vi tror på styrkan i att arbeta tillsammans och rikta vår kollektiva passion mot visionära idéer och skapa bättre lösningar.
Samtidigt får du det bästa paketet av förmåner.
Lön: 40-80k/månad
Semester: 30-60 betalda dagar
Pension: Ja
Försäkringar: Ja
Friskvård: Ja
Visst låter det intressant?
Sök direkt och var med och skapa den framtida historian du vill se när vi tillsammans tar nästa stora steg inom AI!

Title: Data Scientist/MLOps Engineer – Lund
Description:
Data Scientist/MLOps Engineer – Lund
Veritaz is a fast-growing IT-consultant firm. Our company is made up of insanely bright people from over 4 countries, and we are in Sweden, UK, US and Pakistan. The voyage has been incredible this far, but it is only the beginning.

Title: Sommarjobb: Kontor 2023
Description:
Requisition ID: 17270
Category: Administration
Career level: Student
Contract type: Temporary
På SKF eftersträvar vi att ständigt utmana och utveckla verksamheten. Sen 1907, med en innovation som förändrade världen, gör våra lösningar skillnad för miljön och våra kunders verksamhet. Det handlar om en effektiv och tillförlitlig rotation av applikationer, ihop med en cirkulär ekonomi. Det handlar om något större än bara affärer, det handlar om delat ansvar för vår värld. Tillsammans med 43 000 kollegor i 130 länder har du alla möjligheter att få världen att snurra cirkulärt, göra våra kunder nöjda och minska vårt klimatavtryck. Vi kallar det ingenjörskonst.

Är du student och studerar vid högskola eller universitet? Vill du få chansen att arbeta på ett innovativt och globalt företag?

Då borde du söka…
Sommarjobb på SKF

Vi på SKF söker nu sommarjobbare till vårt huvudkontor i Göteborg. Vill du vara med och jobba på ett välkänt och globalt företag med fantastiska kollegor? Då kan det vara just dig vi söker! Enligt oss är det innovativa, förändringsinriktade och passionerade människor som gör att företag förändras och växer sig starkare, och nu har du chansen att vara en del av vår resa!

Hos oss får du möjligheten att arbeta med kollegor över hela världen och bygga ett oslagbart nätverk. Vi erbjuder ett sommarjobb med möjligheten att arbeta inom ett område som ligger nära din utbildning, exempelvis produktutveckling, inköp, ekonomi, HR, kvalitet, kundservice eller processutveckling. Ett sommarjobb på SKF är en perfekt väg in på arbetsmarknaden och kan leda till fortsatt praktikarbete eller anställning.

Vad innebär ett sommarjobb på SKF?

Anställningen sträcker sig ungefär över 6–10 veckor. Arbetstiden är förlagd till dagtid.

Arbetsuppgifterna på tjänstemannasidan beror på arbetsområde. Kanske blir du deltagare i ett projekt, eller så får du egna arbetsuppgifter för att täcka upp under våra medarbetares semesterfrånvaro. Tidigare år har vi bland annat erbjudit tjänster inom följande områden; Purchasing, Customer Service, Supply Chain, Economy, Logistics, Learning & Development, Software Engineering, Data Science samt People Experience.

Vi söker dig som

Studerar på högskola eller universitet
Har goda kunskaper engelska (några tjänster kräver även goda kunskaper i svenska)
Har ett intresse för SKF som organisation
Är en positiv, engagerad och noggrann person

Du ingår i en prioriterad urvalsgrupp om du tidigare sommarjobbat på SKF.

Ansökan
Ansök genom att klicka på knappen "Apply" och följ instruktionerna. Observera att vi inte tar emot ansökningar via mail.

I din ansökan behöver du bifoga ditt CV samt ett Personligt brev.

Sista ansökningsdag är 2023-03-05, men tjänsterna kommer att tillsättas löpande under ansökningstiden. Skicka därför in din ansökan så snart som möjligt för att öka dina chanser, vänta inte!

För frågor gällande rekryteringsprocessen är du välkommen att kontakta hr.support@skf.com.

Vad händer sedan?
Under februari-mars matchar vi inkomna ansökningar mot de behov som organisationen har. Vi kommer att intervjua och erbjuda tjänster mellan februari och april och vi räknar med att avsluta rekryteringsprocessen i början av maj.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
About SKF
SKF’s mission is to be the undisputed leader in the bearing business. SKF offers solutions around the rotating shaft, including bearings, seals, lubrication management, condition monitoring and maintenance services. SKF is represented in more than 130 countries and has around 17,000 distributor locations worldwide. Annual sales in SEK is around 75 billion and the number of employees ca 41,000.

Title: Dutch Speaking Customer Service Agent
Description:
THE OPPORTUNITY
Do you have an interest in fashion, see solutions rather than problems and always strive to provide service at a top level? Then this opportunity might be the one for you.
Do you also value a dynamic and international work environment, fun and knowledgeable colleagues as well as a lot of internal career opportunities, then apply and get the chance to join our amazing Customer Service Team.
As our new Dutch speaking Customer Service Agent you will join a team, where you together will work towards providing world class service to our customers.

WHAT YOU WILL DO
The first part of your journey at Boozt will be to take part in a thorough training program to create the best possible conditions for you to succeed and excel in your new role. Training sessions and development meetings will be held continuously throughout your time at Boozt.
Together with our trainers you will focus on your development and take part in training sessions to tailor your journey as a Boozter.

Provide top class service to our customers with all inquiries coming in via phone, email or chat
Be our expert when it comes to questions ranging from specific product information, to styling tips, stock status, shipping details, payment queries, and campaign errands
You will be the company’s eyes and ears and will be a truly important part of the “from order to delivery chain” to ensure that we reach our goal of building an unrivaled customer experience

YOUR PROFILE
Your native language is Dutch. You are also fluent in English since this is our corporate language and it is a part of your daily tasks to support other markets when needed
You enjoy solving problems, exceeding expectations and has a natural ability to connect with people
You see no obstacles in the challenges of offering quick, informative and individual answers and explanations even in stressful times
Previous experience in the service industry is a plus
Good communication skills and a real interest in expressing yourself well, both in speech and writing (tests will be given as part of our recruitment process)
You are proud of being precise and it is natural for you to be considerate in your behavior both internally and externally

OUR OFFER
This is a chance for you to join our vibrant Customer Service Team, an opportunity to grow and develop with one of the leading Nordic E-commerce companies

Full-time temporary employment for an initial 12 months with the possibility for a permanent position (the employment will start with a 6 month probation period)
Working hours for the team is 8:00-17:00, 10:00-19:00
You working schedule will be published for you to see four months in advance
You will join a big international team where we support and learn from each other, but the most important of all we have fun while doing so

We look forward to your application!

BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?

We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.

Title: Team Lead - Analytics & Data Science
Description:
Why Avaus?
We are the leading marketing and sales transformation partner in the Nordics! We are 120 colleagues located at our offices in Helsinki, Stockholm, Munich, Milan and Gdansk. As a company, we have more than 15 years of experience in data-driven marketing and sales in large organizations across B2C & B2B industries.
Our vision is to become the leading actionable marketing data-asset provider in Europe by 2025. We believe that to survive, companies need to invest heavily in capabilities related to intelligence & AI, customer experience, personalisation and change management. Our mission is to foster customer-centric organizations equipped to grow and face the future. Our own future growth is heavily driven by activating data and analytics for our clients.
The Team
The Analytics team at Avaus consists of data scientists, BI & CRM analysts, and is a team of highly skilled and ambitious people, eager to improve our clients’ results by providing them with better decisions and actions based on data. We work in a wide range of tools and languages to orchestrate and automate the activation of customer data. We are a social crew and enjoy working closely together and learning from one another.


The role
As the Team Lead for our Analytics team, you will be responsible for managing team development plans, coach and guide team members and assist our operations matching the right person for projects. You will also be responsible for the team's career development, recruitment, resourcing and establishing a culture in line with Avaus cultural cornerstones. As a team lead you will need to be a trusted role model for your team and among your peers. Apart from leading your team, you’re also expected to act as a subject-matter expert in client projects. You will most likely be doing some of these things also:
People & team management
Performance reviews and dito assessments, including salary reviews
Coaching of individuals and teams
Personal & career development plans and execution
Competence area customer delivery and subject matter expertise
Team building
Operations & resourcing
Contribute to sales cases within competence area
1-1:s and individual follow-up
Participate in building a growth mindset and culture within the organization
Thought-leadership around the selected topic, both internally and externally


Who are you?
For this role, we are primarily looking for someone with strong leadership skills. It’s preferable if you have experience within marketing automation, CRM Marketing, Content automation and consulting in general. The role will also include supporting client projects and helping clients define and execute on personalization strategies.
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree within a relevant field
Multiple years of relevant work experience, preferably within consulting
Consultancy mindset and the ability to work in fast paced environments
Proven track record within people and team leadership
Extensive experience in data, analytics and reporting
Fluent in Swedish, as our customers require us to communicate in Swedish
Fluent in English
Practical information
This is a permanent position with a 6 months’ probation period, based at our Stockholm office at Katarinavägen 17. Starting date as soon as possible or by agreement. We offer a hybrid remote workplace and you will report to Head of Delivery.
Already feel like one of us? Send your applications in English as soon as possible, but no later than 2023-02-28. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Paola Banegas, Head of Talant. Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page.
We look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Who we are
Monto, part of Fortnox, is now looking for a Data Scientist!
Monto is on a mission to ensure that all small and medium sized businesses (SMEs) are able to access financing on fair terms. We want to level the playing field between SMEs and Enterprises by helping lenders become better at serving their SME customers. By leveling up lenders, helping them make use of real time accounting and financial data we will help them to help SMEs and thereby close the financing gap in the market. We are boosting the business of SMEs which will fuel the economy!
We are looking to hire great people, who are passionate about using their talents to generate success. We are currently looking for a Data Scientist to better understand, segment and predict customer’s behavior and their financial states.
Who you are
We are looking for ambitious people with a sense of ownership and responsibility. We need problem solvers, initiative takers, people that see opportunities and potential to improve. You will play an important role in taking Monto to the next level - thus, you should desire to go above and beyond to deliver and grow as an individual. At Monto we embrace change, you should dare to challenge the status quo and be persistent in doing so.
Moreover we believe that you are passionate about data science and want to be a part of Monto Data Science helping companies get access to financing based on their true real time behavior and financial data.
You have:
Knowledge of machine learning and statistics
Python and SQL programming skills
Experience developing ML models.
Strong communication skills and the ability to connect the findings to our business
Experienced with AWS is a plus
What’s in it for you?
You will be working in a multicultural team with other data scientists and ML engineers, creating machine learning solutions to add intelligence and automation to Monto’s SaaS platform. Our team owns our products end-to-end, including generating, extracting and preprocessing data, as well as developing, deploying, and monitoring our models.
Specifically you will:
Design, develop, and monitor next-gen ML solutions
Translate business and data needs to technical requirements, then work with other teams to ensure correct implementation
Work closely with product designers and developers to scope and design our products and identify potential new opportunities
Contribute to the team with your mathematical skills and modeling abilities
If you share our passion, join us in making the world a better place for small and medium businesses!
About Monto & Fortnox:
Monto is part of Fortnox AB (publ), a business platform that connects people, companies and organizations. We help companies start, grow and develop. With smart technical products, solutions and services, and the opportunity to connect them with hundreds of external parties, we are a hub for businesses in Sweden. Our vision is to create a prosperous society shaped by successful companies. Fortnox was founded in 2001 and has headquarters in Växjö and offices in Malmö, Linköping and Stockholm. The share is listed on Nasdaq Stockholm. For further information see www.fortnox.se

Are you curious about Monto's story? Read more about us here.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
About Froda
Froda was founded in 2015 with a clear vision – to revolutionize the banking experience for entrepreneurs by making it easy and affordable for them to invest in their ideas. Today, we are one of Sweden's fastest growing fintech with major international growth plans. We are a creative tech company with the ambition to turn a historically expensive and unfair industry into something ethical, sustainable, and forward thinking. Behind the company are several well-known investors and talents from e.g., Avanza, Spotify, Google, and Klarna.

About the Role
Froda is at the unique point of taking our data analytics and real-time decisioning to the next level. We are now looking for our next Data Scientist to help us transform our data into actionable insights.

You will design, develop, and maintain statistical data models in collaboration with our chief data scientist as well as our data engineers and analysts. Besides working with modeling you will also build and work on the data pipelines which feed our models.

This is a key role in evolving Froda's data strategy as well as in the development and realization of our data platform.

Who are you?
We believe that you are a curious person who enjoys working in a team with other eager and open-minded people, who can’t wait to learn more and share their knowledge. You are driven by finding the right solution, in a business-oriented manner. We want you to be fluent in English and Swedish for this role, and to have a master's degree preferably in engineering, mathematics, or statistical modeling.
When it comes to your tech skills, we believe that you have experience of:
At least a couple of years as a Data Scientist or a similar role,
Working with statistical modeling in either Python, R, or similar,
Working extensively with SQL.
If you also have worked with machine learning, credit modeling, and maybe have programmed some in C#, Java, or similar, it is of course a plus!
So, what’s in it for you?
You will have the opportunity to work hands-on in a fast-paced, exciting, and collaborative scale-up company with ambitious co-workers that also honors the work-life balance. To add an edge to our employee offer we also have a warrant program for everybody working here.
At Froda, you will truly have freedom under responsibility, which means that you will have the ability to impact your own work and tackle a wider set of tasks than in a typical data science role. You have the actual possibilities to impact tech strategy and decisions. We are a passionate team with an open culture, and we truly believe that the best decisions are taken by combining people's knowledge!

If you have any questions or thoughts concerning the role or process, don’t hesitate to send me an email at: john@froda.se.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
What is this about?
Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions. We understand how Computer Vision and AI can benefit the society. We stand ready to use our expertise to facilitate businesses in their journey into the era of AI. We work with several clients with various industry fields in close collaboration with top universities in Sweden.

Synteda is actively working on several unique products and solutions in various fields. Dream-innovate-create is our work process were our ideas go through different stages. We create successful solutions by checking feasibility of our product idea (POC) and develop our solution working with agile methodologies until we reach a complete full-scale product.

Synteda has a core team of highly qualified experts that provide assessment to identify challenges and explore different ideas to enhance effectiveness and develop specific algorithms to overcome company challenges. Synteda is built on ethical awareness, curiosity, transparency, respect, participation and last but not least science.

Synteda is growing rapidly and we are looking for a talented data scientist to join our team of experts.
What are we looking for?
Responsibilities
Work on our various platforms and customer assignments.
Collaborate with data scientists and help them test and develop new algorithms.
Enhance existing applications and platforms.
Research, build and implement new solutions.
Build and analyze new data models.
Application of optimization techniques to previous projects.
Analyze multi-variable data sets.
Adopt best practices and share them across the team.

Skills
Bachelor’s, Master’s, or Ph.D. degree in computer science or similar.
Programming experience in combination of Python, C#, C/C++, Spark, Java/Scala.
Knowledge of scientific computing language such as Matlab or R.
Exposure to big data platforms such as AWS, Azure, Hadoop.
Good knowledge of relevant data science packages such as Numpy, PyTorch, Tensorflow, Scipy, Pandas and basic mathematical modelling.
Experience in big data tools such as ElasticSearch/Soir and Kafka.
Experience creating ETL/ELT processes.
Experience with Databricks and Azure tools.
Knowledge of AI and machine learning models.
Good understanding of data engineering practices and data modelling.
Solid experience in multi-variable analysis.
You have experience working with large data sets and distributed computing tools.
Previous experience building machine learning models and data visualization.
Experience of agile development methodologies.
Fluent in English, both spoken and written is required.
Advantage with Swedish.

Title: Junior ESG Analyst
Description:
Junior ESG Analyst
THE OPPORTUNITY
Are you passionate about environmental, social, and governance (ESG) issues and want to make a positive impact on the organization? Do you have a strong analytical mind and the ability to think critically about complex issues? If so, we have an exciting opportunity for you to join our team as a Junior ESG Analyst.
Boozt is one of the Nordics’ leading e-commerce companies and therefore also wants to be the leading role model for e-commerce businesses within fashion, beauty, and lifestyle. You treasure what you measure and we strongly believe in a sustainable business model where we use all our resources as responsibly as we can; natural resources, financial resources, and human resources.
As a Junior ESG Analyst, you will be conducting research and analysis on our e-commerce business to asses the ESG performance of our operations. You will work closely with senior team members to identify and evaluate ESG risks and opportunities and help develop recommendations for improving our performance. In addition, you will have the chance to contribute to the development of ESG-related reports and presentations, as well as engage with stakeholders to discuss and promote the importance of ESG.
Do you want to join our amazing team and have the opportunity to work on meaningful projects that contribute to a more sustainable and socially responsible organization?
WHAT YOU WILL DO
Identify, collect and analyze data to help us assess the environmental performance of our operations
Focus on data collection of Packaging, Waste, Energy, Distribution
Prepare data and KPIs for external and internal ESG reporting
Be a key stakeholder in related projects that focus on different aspects of ESG, often together with our Sustainability Manager
Follow the development of ESG standards and frameworks such as GHG Protocol, ESRS, and Extended Producer Responsibility
YOUR PROFILE
To be successful in this role you will have a strong sustainability interest. You have strong analytical skills and the ability to communicate complex ideas effectively. You are detail-oriented and structured, but also a responsible and independent team player with the ability to multitask in a busy environment.
Bachelor's degree in a related field such as environmental studies, sustainability, finance, or business
Strong Excel skills
Experience in Environmental reporting or sustainability is a plus
Good communication skills with both internal and external stakeholders
Advanced level of the Swedish language
Fluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered)
_Please apply for this position as soon as possible as we work with ongoing selection and interviews. The first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.

IT Support

As an IT Supporter at Boozt you will be working closely with the business teams to help and enable their work. Here you will be a part of a small, international and friendly team that loves providing good service to the rest of the organization. Student Assistant | Buying & Merchandising

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Do you want to be a part of a new Analytics Operations team and get to work in an inspiring environment? Then you should keep reading!
DevPort are now looking for a Data Analyst to join our clients new Analytics Operations team. The Analytics Operations team should act as a catalyst and take responsibility for analytics value creation in all phases; from early ideation with stakeholders to creating runtime dashboards and data pipelines or guiding superusers to help them create their own dashboards. We also cooperate with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to run AI/ML models in operations. The Analytics Operations team is new and as such you will be part of developing the unit and creating successful use cases.
Our clients new Data, Analytics & AI organization is focused on unleashing the value of data collected from connected customer assets. The team are set out to drive the transformation into a data driven culture, where Data, Analytics & AI/ML are an integral part in their services and internal processes. By spanning across Data Foundation, Data Analytics and Data Science they can provide their stakeholders with actionable insights and take ownership of the whole process from ideation and exploration to analytics operations.

About the role
Drive the data journey by connecting with stakeholders, running workshops, identify opportunities and take it from idea to value.
Develop state-of-the art solutions, dashboards, and insight reports.
Stay at the forefront in the analytics space and share knowledge and experience with colleagues.

Your profile
You have a degree in a relevant field or practical experience from utilizing data to drive change.
You are a creative, entrepreneurial problem-solver with an inquisitive attitude and are not afraid of complex challenges or unconventional approaches.
You routinely use dashboarding as a tool for problem solving, and are experienced in at least one dashboarding solution (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, QuickSight, Grafana).
You confidently and systematically build analysis approaches from scratch, including data extraction, scripting and/or programming in relevant languages and analysis with creation of informative and appealing visualizations.
You are a communicative person that builds and maintains trust with stakeholders and colleagues.
Humorous; because, in the end, working in the team should be fun.

What can we offer you?
You will be part of a highly skilled analytics team that together with our stakeholders creates great value in short- and long-term engagements. In this team you will be able to make a data-driven impact on sustainable transport solutions for our client, their customers and society at large - and have fun while doing it. Your workplace will be based in Lindholmen in Gothenburg.

Application
Apply by following the steps below. If you have any questions regarding the position, send an email to Elin Thulin at elin.thulin@devport.se
I am looking forward to read you application!

About DevPort
DevPort is a technology consulting company in an expansive development phase with headquarter in Gothenburg and offices in Stockholm, Linköping, Helsingborg and Karlskrona. DevPort has its core competence in the automotive industry and employs more than 500 people in three business areas - Digital solutions, production development and product development.
We are proud of our employees and of collaborating with several of the world's leading vehicle manufacturers, companies in the defense industry and other development-intensive industries.
We are characterized by a family culture with entrepreneurship, competence, security and a community that infuses the company's operations and contributes to a pleasant and inspiring workplace.

Title: Data Scientist in Predictive Computational Chemistry and Machine Learning
Description:
Do you have expertise in, and passion for, deriving knowledge from data and computational modelling? Would you like to apply your expertise to implement transformative Artificial Intelligent and Machine Learning based methods to drive the digital transformation in a company that follows the science and turns ideas into life changing medicines? Then AstraZeneca might be of interest to you!
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are
empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
Pharmaceutical Sciences at AstraZeneca delivers the therapies of the future through scientific leadership in drug delivery, design of synthetic routes, and manufacturing of Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients and drug products. In essence, we are working “from molecule to medicine” to develop medicines for our patients today and tomorrow.
The Data Science and Modelling department within Pharmaceutical Sciences is developing a digital transformation strategy to drive innovation, optimization of the drug development process and data-driven decision making.
We now have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Scientist or Associate Principal Scientist, depending on your background and experience, in our Data Science – Substance team. This role can be based in either Gothenburg, Sweden or Macclesfield, United Kingdom.
What you’ll do
In this role you will get the opportunity to engage with key internal and external stakeholders to identify and validate impactful solutions to provide scientific leadership and drive innovation. You will work at the forefront of the digital transformation within AstraZeneca, turning ideas into life changing medicines for patients!
Typical responsibilities in this role
Use a combination of data driven models and molecular modelling to predict and elucidate chemical structures of impurities and degradants of pharmaceutical substances as well as formulated drug products.
Identify and utilize internal and external data sources and test, develop, and implement new combinations of machine learning and mechanistic modelling workflows to predict physical chemical properties and drug substance reactivity to be used by other scientists
Support drug project campaigns with expert insights on chemical reactivity, stability, and catalysis
Essential requirements
PhD in computational chemistry or equivalent experience
Track record of applying molecular modelling to druglike molecules
Proven experience of using machine learning to build predictive models
Skills and experience in modelling of chemical reactivity and analytical chemistry data
Good knowledge of Python programming including machine learning frameworks such as TensorFlow, Scikit-learn as well as cheminformatics packages such as, RDkit.
Knowledge of end-to-end software such as PipelinePilot, Knime or Dataiku is beneficial.
Excellent communication skills, written and spoken
Self-motivated
Team player
Why AstraZeneca
At AstraZeneca, we turn ideas into life changing medicines and strive to continuously meet the unmet needs of patients worldwide. Working here means being entrepreneurial, thinking big, and working together to make the impossible a reality. Ultimately, it’s more than a job. We know that our work impacts people with serious conditions, many of whom have no other alternatives. That’s what drives us – the potential to impact over one billion patients worldwide.
So, what’s next?
Are you already imagining yourself joining us? Good, because we can’t wait to hear from you! Welcome with your application; CV and cover letter, no later than February 27th .
For more information, please contact recruiting manager Christof Jäger, PhD at
Linkedin Christof Jäger
To read more about the department and Data Science & AI at AstraZeneca, please visit Data Science & Artificial Intelligence AstraZeneca
Competitive salary and benefits package on offer.

Title: Senior Analytics Manager
Description:
At Storytel we believe that powerful stories add an extra dimension to life.
Storytel is one of the world’s leading audiobook and ebook streaming services and we offer unlimited listening to consumers in 25+ markets.
Our vision is to make the world a more empathetic place with great stories to be shared and enjoyed by anyone, anywhere, anytime

About the Role
As a Senior Analytics Manager, you will be responsible for leading a growing team of analysts in the scoping and execution of data and analytics projects that support the product strategy and the successful growth of the company. You will develop analytical solutions powered by a modern data stack in a dynamic environment where you will have the opportunity to directly impact how we work with data across the organization. You will, over time, shape the team and capabilities towards a truly federated operational model for analytics.
If you're a data-driven, empathic leader with strong communication skills and a passion for driving positive change through data-driven decision making, you would be a great fit for our team. Join us and play a key role in driving the growth of one of the world's leading audiobook and ebook streaming services.

What you’ll do
Lead, manage and grow a team of data analysts
Support the team to drive impact by prioritizing projects with highest business opportunity and/or of long term strategic importance while managing stakeholders expectations
Mentor the team on data & analytics technical skills, career development and stakeholder management
Collaborate closely with and influence business and product staff and leaders as part of multidisciplinary teams to assess analytics opportunities and develop data and analytics products and solutions
Partner closely with peers and stakeholders within the data science engineering domain, broader engineering and product to support the successful end-to-end delivery of analyses and solutions
Continuously collaborate with stakeholders to ensure data insights and solutions are incorporated in a day-to-day decision making, OKR planning and strategic prioritization
Work closely with the data engineering team to support our efforts in delivering self service analytics solutions, appropriate data pipelines and documentation and capabilities to the community of analytics users
Support Storytel’s efforts in becoming a data-led organization through capability building, adoption of new tooling, data literacy initiatives and supporting teams develop a data-first mindset in their workflows

About You
To succeed in this role, we believe that:
You have a background in a quantitative discipline such as Computer Science, Engineering, Information Science, Statistics or a related field
You have 7+ years of experience in analytics
You have several years of hands-on experience in SQL, R, Python and data visualization tools
You have few years of experience in directly managing data analytics team
You are an empathic leader, who enjoys mentoring and coaching others You are highly adaptable and can successfully uncover and navigate greenfield analytics projects
You have a deep interest and enthusiasm for working with data and are highly motivated to drive positive change in organizations through data-driven decision making
You have strong communication skills to partner with stakeholders effectively and are able to successfully bridge with non-technical audiences

Bonus if you have one or more of the following:
Advanced relevant degree
Experience in analytics management from product and/or growth companies
Hands-on modeling experience (statistical modeling, forecasting, A/B testing, etc)
Experience with the modern data stack and cloud technologies Experience with experimentation frameworks and platforms

What we offer
At Storytel we trust our employees and believe in their autonomy. We offer flexible working hours, remote working possibilities when possible and flexible public holidays for people to celebrate what they truly believe in.
Storytel’s culture encourages self-leadership, innovation, collaboration – and our employees share a common passion for high-quality content and stories. There is a strong emphasis on continuous development, learning through experimentation and actively sharing feedback to constantly improve performance.
Storytel offers a friendly, entrepreneurial and fast-moving work environment where new ideas and creativity are welcomed. We like doing things in new ways and questioning old methods. The Storytel culture - characterized by being welcoming and helpful - is important to us. We don’t believe in hierarchy and micromanagement; we highly believe in giving responsibility and having people grow alongside it. And of course - you get unlimited listening to audio and ebooks from our service!
Does this sound like you? If you feel like Storytel is a place where you could thrive, please submit your application in English and we will contact you as soon as possible.

Title: Data Insight Expert/Data Scientist in Pharmaceutical Sciences
Description:
We harness digital, data science & AI to fast-forward our research. Making sure work born in a lab can make a real difference. Everyday, impacting patients’ lives across the world.
What we do
AstraZeneca is a global, science-driven biopharmaceutical business and our innovative medicines are used by millions of patients worldwide. Ultimately, our aim is to work towards a cure for some of the world’s most complex diseases. Whether that’s by shaping the patient ecosystem and focusing on outcomes, or by progressing potential medicines and accelerating their launch.
Pharmaceutical Sciences at AstraZeneca delivers the therapies of the future through scientific leadership in drug delivery, design of synthetic routes, and manufacturing of Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients and drug products. In essence, we are working “from molecule to medicine” to develop medicines for our patients today and tomorrow.
The Data Science and Modelling department within Pharmaceutical Sciences is developing a digital transformation strategy to drive innovation, optimization of the drug development process and data-driven decision making.
We now have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Scientist or Associate Principal Scientist, depending on your background and experience in our data science Product team based in Gothenburg, Sweden.
What you’ll do
In this role, you will get the opportunity to engage with key internal and external stakeholders to identify and validate impactful solutions to provide scientific leadership and drive innovation. Our team interacts with many functions within the company such as chemistry, formulation work, drug delivery, analytical sciences and solid-state development meaning you will have a diverse set of interactions and impact possibilities. You will simply be at the forefront of the digital transformation within AstraZeneca, turning ideas into life changing medicines for patients!
Typical responsibilities in this role
Together with scientific experts develop a strategy to extract and capture data, perform analysis, and be able to use the information to support drug project development decisions.
Utilize Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to build predictive models to generate knowledge in a diverse set of drug development areas
Develop and implement proof-of-concept algorithms, models, workflows and visualizations to be used by other scientists
Act as a role model and mentor to scientists with less experience in machine learning and to champion FAIR data practices
Develop training material and provide training to AstraZeneca user groups
Plan, write and publish high quality scientific papers.
Essential requirements
PhD in computational chemistry, data science, informatics, physics or similar
Track record of applying knowledge graphs, text mining, and natural-language processing
Proven experience of using machine learning to build predictive models
Understanding of natural science, preferably in the field of chemistry or chemoinformatics
Strong record in Python programming including machine learning frameworks such as TensorFlow, Scikit-learn as well as cheminformatics packages such as, RDkit.
Knowledge of end-to-end software such as PipelinePilot, Knime or Dataiku is beneficial.
Excellent communication skills, written and spoken
Self-motivated
Team player
Why AstraZeneca
At AstraZeneca, we turn ideas into life changing medicines and strive to continuously meet the unmet needs of patients worldwide. Working here means being entrepreneurial, thinking big, and working together to make the impossible a reality. Ultimately, it’s more than a job. We know that our work impacts people with serious conditions, many of whom have no other alternatives. That’s what drives us – the potential to impact over one billion patients worldwide.

Title: Working Student
Description:
IQVIA är ett globalt, ledande företag med fokus på hälsodata, teknologi och avancerad analys. IQVIA arbetar med alla aktörer inom hälso- och sjukvårdssektorn; från läkemedels- och medicinteknikföretag till landsting och myndigheter, både i Sverige och globalt, med visionen att stödja dessa aktörer och vara med och bidra till att föra utvecklingen framåt. IQVIA har kontor i Nordens alla 4 länder med 500+ anställda i regionen.
Om tjänsten
Nu söker vi en student som vill jobba extra under studietiden, i en roll med fokus på marknadsundersökningar och relaterade aktiviteter. Arbetsuppgifterna kommer innebära support i olika uppdrag åt våra kunder inom hälso- och sjukvårdssektorn.
IQVIA är en flexibel arbetsplats, så du är välkommen att arbeta där det passar dig bäst – hemifrån och/eller från vårt kontor i Solna.
Tillexempel kommer du att:
Bistå i arbetet med kvalitativa och kvantitativa analyser samt rapporter och presentationer av olika typer av hälsodata.
Arbeta med administrativa uppgifter vid uppstart av medicinska studier, så som interaktion med sites.
Genomföra djupintervjuer per telefon med läkare, patienter och andra intressenter inom hälso- och sjukvårdsområdet.
Sammanfatta kvalitativa resonemang och ge struktur till källmaterial med varierande ursprung.
Vi ser gärna att du:
Har en Kandidatexamen inom Hälsovetenskap, Biomedicin, Farmaci/Farmakologi eller likvärdigt.
Talar och skriver flytande svenska och engelska.
Har ett intresse för dataanalys samt goda kunskaper i Excel och PowerPoint.
Har grundläggande kunskaper om svensk hälso- och sjukvård och dess aktörer, liksom de globala och lokala läkemedels- och medicinteknikföretag som är verksamma på den svenska marknaden.
Har möjlighet att arbeta 5 – 10 timmar per vecka parallellt med dina studier. Arbetstiderna är flexibla och kan anpassas efter dina studier.
Om du är student med fokus på något område inom hälso- och sjukvård, och vill ha ett meningsfullt och meriterande deltidsjobb under studietiden – sök nu!!
Du är varmt välkommen med din ansökan!
IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions and clinical research services to the life sciences industry. We believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com

Title: CNS / Neuropsychiatric Rater - Helsingborg, Sweden
Description:
As part of the conducting of a clinical study in the field of Schizophrenia, we are looking for an experienced CNS / Neuropsychiatric Rater.
This role, with an immediate start for 6 months in part-time (flexible hours) is to support the site in Helsingborg.
Responsibilities will include:
Administer clinical rating scales s to support the diagnosis and assessment of symptom severity of subjects participating in CNS clinical studies.
Attends, completes, and qualifies for study-specific rater training and certification for trials on which they rate.
Measures the severity of symptoms of study participants
Continuously observe the study participants using approved assessments throughout study
Reports to and works under the guidance of the principal investigator and/or sub-investigator for the study site where the study participant is seen
Assist team in management and assessment of adverse events
Support PI/Sub-I and study coordinators with assessments, data clarification, and data query completion
We are looking for candidates with the following skills and experience: -
Degree in Psychology, Neuropsychology or in Medicine
Qualified candidates must have a minimum of 2 years' experience performing psychometric rating scales for clinical trials.
Solid teamwork, organizational, interpersonal, attention to detail, and problem-solving skills.
Strong written and verbal communication skills
Ability to work under time constraints, and work both independently and cooperatively with interdisciplinary teams
IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions and clinical research services to the life sciences industry. We believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com

Title: PR Leader
Description:
Who you are

You are a highly strategic and analytical person with strong knowledge of using insights to formulate communication plans and with experience developing and leading communication campaigns. You know how to secure communication outcomes related to reaching business goals and how to analyse and influence the result.

For the past 7 years you have worked in media relations, corporate and commercial PR in an international environment both in agencies and inhouse, and during this time you have gained rich experience in developing and brining to life PR strategies.

You demonstrate entrepreneurial spirit and strong leadership skills, by using sound judgements to make timely and effective decisions and comfortably support and influence senior business leaders and colleagues with the business goals in focus. You bring knowledge of how to leverage data science and analytics as well as communication performance measurement tools to perform analyses and gain actionable insights for business decision making and able to evaluate the communication initiatives.

Additionally, you have:

Up-to-date knowledge of media landscape (including the latest trends in social media), activation and measurements.
Knowledge of the area commercial and corporate PR and Media Relations
Solid experience with crisis communication
Passion towards communication and its ability to be a business driver
Affinity with creating engaging communication and working with media relations and stakeholder management

A day in your life with us

As the PR Leader at Ingka Centres you will lead and drive effective and engaging PR and communication, supporting Ingka Centres’ business agenda and contributing to the positioning of Ingka Centres and our brands in people’s hearts and minds.

You will lead development and implementation of PR strategy and plans (commercial and corporate), in alignment with the global communication plan, commercial calendar, and in collaboration with Commercial & Digital Domain and Meeting place teams. You will be part of Ingka Centres global press office, take part in the duty media relations rota and contribute to the development and delivery of Ingka Centres Media Relations agenda.

A PR Leader at Ingka Centres empowers our leaders to be inspiring communicators – identify, train and support spokespersons and, together with Co-worker communication team, develop and execute pro-active engagement plans for key spokespeople. You will collaborate with Ingka Group global press-office, especially with global Media-on-duty team and will develop and strengthen Ingka Centres’ communication preparedness for reputational issues, risks and crisis.

Amongst other things you will:

Lead and drive ideation, activation and execution across earned media for commercial campaigns to maximize commercial impact and drive business results, in close collaboration with the Marketing team and Meeting places
Monitor and analyse media to measure results as well as identify proactive opportunities and potential risk issues related to Ingka Centres, its brands and concepts
Provide active day-to-day support and direction for Meeting places around PR and Communication, with support from Communication Business Partners and the Media Relations team
Work actively across communication priorities to support a 360-communication agenda

In this role you will report to Tatiana Rusakova, our Media Relations and Public Affairs Manager, and be based in Malmo in Sweden.

Together as a team

Together with IKEA Retail and Ingka Investments, Ingka Centres is part of Ingka Group.

As a long-term partner of IKEA, we share our vision, our culture and our values, while what makes our businesses different is the way we fulfil our vision. If the idea of IKEA is to create a better life at home, we work hard to create a better everyday life outside of the home by developing virtual and physical meeting places where people can meet shop and connect with their communities.

We have big plans for the future that involve expanding to new locations, opening smaller-scale concepts closer to the city centres, digitalization, and most of all, living up to shared sustainability goals. We’re constantly looking for energetic, purpose-led and creative people who’d like to join us on our journey to create meeting places around the world.

Sounds exciting? There’s a lot more to know about us! Take a look at our website, read our stories and try to imagine how you can be part of our team helping us reach our goals!

www.ingkacentres.com

This role belongs to Communication domain. The Purpose of our function is to build love and trust in our brands and our meeting places, with all the people we want to reach, in order to drive growth.

Questions and support? Let's connect!

Perhaps there is something you´re wondering about? For job specific questions please contact hiring manager Tatiana Rusakova at tatiana.rusakova@ingka.com.

Do you have questions about the recruitment process? Please contact Hektor Thomke at hektor.thomke@ingka.com

We encourage you to apply as soon as possible, though no later than 2023-02-06.

We look forward to receiving your application!

Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions.
