Title: Chef Data Science
Description:
Arbetsuppgifter
Leda avdelningen Data Science
Äga och driva SBABs Data Science-strategi
Förstärka och förädla SBABs datadrivna arbetssätt
Inspirera och driva innovation inom data och avancerad analys
Är du nyfiken på hur den här texten ska sluta? Kul! Vi gillar dig redan. Att vara nyfiken är viktigt för oss.

På SBAB spelar nämligen rollen mindre roll. Att du är kunnig förväntar vi oss. Det viktiga är att du vill vara med och bidra till vår kultur, attityd och vårt sätt att vara. Och eftersom vi är lika många experter som medarbetare, behöver alla vara just nyfikna och intresserade av varandras olikheter. Vi lyssnar in och omvärderar kontinuerligt. Vi tror på mångfald, att olika perspektiv berikar och att du är en viktig framgångsfaktor. Fortfarande nyfiken? Välkommen!
Att jobba som Chef Data Science
I rollen som Chef Data Science så driver du arbetet inom data- och analysområdet men ser även till att vi ligger i framkant med vår tekniska plattform. Vi förväntar oss att du har en brinnande passion för både analys och teknik.
Data Science har en central och strategisk roll på SBAB och jobbar integrerat med hela verksamheten och består av tre enheter med olika verksamhetsfokus, totalt ca 45 medarbetare. Vi jobbar i en hybridlösning där en stor del av vår data ligger i ett on-premise datawarehouse baserat på SQL Server. Vi har också komponenter i en privat molnlösning med ett mål att flytta stora delar av plattformen till ett publikt moln. Vi har en väldefinierad teknisk roadmap och en teknisk vision som du behöver fortsätta driva mot.

Du har en strategisk höjd och en förmåga att se hur data kan skapa kund- och affärsvärde i en verksamhet. För att lyckas i rollen tror vi att du har en praktisk bakgrund inom business intelligence och avancerad analys samt en välutvecklad social förmåga att nätverka och skapa kontakter tvärs igenom organisationen. Du har en stor förmåga att inspirera till innovation samt identifiera nya möjligheter att förädla och effektivisera verksamheten med hjälp av data. Du är en möjliggörare som kan skapa rätt förutsättningar för våra autonoma team att leverera affärsnytta.

Som person är du en prestigelös, modig och tillitsfull ledare som brinner för både analys och teknik men framförallt de värden som uppstår i en datadriven verksamhet. Du gillar högt tempo och agerar direkt men tummar inte på kvalitet. Du tar ansvar och samarbetar samtidigt som du vågar utmana och tänka nytt.

Chef Data Science ingår i Techs ledningsgrupp och rapporterar till CTO. Placeringsort för denna roll är Solna och rollen kräver att du talar svenska.

Har du check på allt?
Omtänksam
Lagspelare
Målmedveten
Självdrivande
Ansvarstagande
Annars då?
Gillar du oss, och tror att du kan bidra, är vårt tips att inte vänta för länge med att skicka in CV eller LinkedIn-profil. Har du andra idéer på hur du kan visa vem du är? Spännande! Hur du än ansöker så ser vi fram emot att lära känna dig mer.

Title: Corporate Communications Specialist
Description:
Corporate Communications Specialist
THE OPPORTUNITY
Are you looking for an exciting opportunity to put your communication skills into play and create great results in one of the leading e-commerce companies in the Nordics?
We are looking for an ambitious and energetic Communications Specialist to join our small and dynamic Corporate Communications team at our headquarters in Hyllie, Malmö.
In close collaboration with fellow Boozters, you will support corporate reputation initiatives around our vision of becoming the leading responsible Nordic Department Store. In your role, you will work closely with various Boozt teams– including the executive leadership – in crafting meaningful messages that position Boozt strongly internally and externally.
This is a unique opportunity for you looking to work at the intersection of commerce and communication in a company with colleagues from all over the world that encourages you to grow.
WHAT YOU WILL DO
Your primary goal is to support our team in promoting the Boozt vision and related key messages to generate an even stronger brand position amongst Boozt stakeholders.
Tasks will include:
Contribute to a differentiated and engaging media position to elevate overall brand awareness and reputation by lifting Boozt key messaging into news cycles and targeted media.
Create compelling thought leadership through inspiring opinion pieces that will lift conversations and get Boozt positively noticed in the media.
Generate and author a variety of engaging external and internal communications including content such as press releases, blog posts, articles, FAQs, media statements, talking points, social media posts, and keynote presentations.
Collaborate closely and assist various Boozt teams in making sure all our great stories and milestones come to life both externally and internally.
YOUR PROFILE
To succeed in this position, it is essential that you are both a skilled communicator and a strong collaborator – with a sharp pen and a commercial mindset. You are caring, committed, and a great team player. You are not afraid to question the status quo and are ready to jump into action when and wherever needed.
Since Boozt is a truly international company, you will be involved in cross-cultural collaboration. Our corporate language is English meaning great written and oral English skills are crucial.
*
You hold a master's degree in communications, journalism, PR and have a minimum of 2-4 years of experience from an in-house Corporate Communications team or a PR agency
You have worked with media relations in a constantly evolving media landscape and gained a detailed understanding of earned media channels and what makes a story interesting to reporters.
An interest in the e-commerce industry and a fascination with how technology is driving business forward is a plus.
Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.
Welcome to apply for the position!
BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor
A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania, and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal-opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Business Development Representative - Data Analytics
Description:
Transforming the Future with the Convergence of Simulation and Data
Business Development Representative – Data Analytics SaaS Nordics
Lund, Sweden
Do you like a challenge, are you a complex thinker who likes to solve problems? If so, then you might be the new Altairian we are searching for. At Altair, your curiosity matters. We pride ourselves on a business culture that enables open, creative thinking, and we deeply value our employees and their contributions towards our clients' success, as well as our own.

Job Summary:
The Altair Data Analytics team is looking for a Business Development Representative to help generate new business. This is an exciting opportunity to work in a growing company currently developing new technology.
Altair offers a highly advanced and powerful data analytics solution for businesses in the areas of data preparation, data science, and data visualisation. Our customers use our products to solve their business problems, and generate deeper insight from their data, resulting in increased efficiency and profitability.

BDRs are responsible for proactive inbound/outbound prospecting, lead/contact management and pipeline building. This position will have a direct impact on our success by providing qualified prospects to AE’s for Opportunity creation. As a member of the BDR Team you will be joining a fast-paced close nit group that thrive in a competitive environment. You will partner with AE’s across the organisation to create new selling opportunities in key targeted accounts across multiple industry verticals.
In this role, you will be provided the guidance and training needed to become a technology sales expert while mastering the art of the cold call and the finesse of targeted email campaigns. You will actively collaborate with marketing and sales executives to develop the best ways to grow the AE’s Pipeline. If you are looking to master your sales skills, grow as a sales professional and launch your sales career, this is the opportunity for you.

What You Will Need:
Basics:
If you have at least 1-2 years’ experience in a sales role (or similar) where you can demonstrate successes and wins as well as fluency in one of the Scandinavian languages, (Swedish, Norwegian or Danish) or Finnish, and English, you could be our next Altairian! We also value software sales experience as well as enterprise and financial services industry knowledge.
Ideally, you will have experience in the following areas:
Lead generation & qualification
Account mapping
Campaign building
Working internationally (Nordic territory)
Cold calling, 40+ calls a day
CRM, Microsoft Office

How You Will Be Successful:
Envision the Future
Communicate Honestly and Broadly
Seek Technology and Business “Firsts”
Embrace Diversity and Take Risks

What We Offer:
Work actively for employeés health/wellness
High team spirit
Smaller companies locally but part of a global group
Unique expert knowledge
Hybrid working model
Competitive salary

Why Work with Us:
Altair is a global technology company providing software and cloud solutions in the areas of product development, high-performance computing (HPC) and artificial intelligence (AI). Altair enables organizations in nearly every industry to compete more effectively in a connected world, while creating a more sustainable future. With more than 3,000 engineers, scientists and creative thinkers in 25 countries, we help solve our customer’s toughest challenges and deliver unparalleled service, helping the innovators innovate, drive better decisions, and turn today’s problems into tomorrow’s opportunities.

Our vision is to transform customer decision making with data analytics, simulation, and high-performance computing and artificial intelligence (AI).
For more than 30 years, we have been helping our customers integrate electronics and controls with mechanical design to expand product value, develop AI, simulation and data-driven digital twins to drive better decisions, and deliver advanced HPC and cloud solutions to support unlimited idea exploration.

Ready to go? #ONLYFORWARD
At our core we are explorers; adventurers; pioneers. We are the brains behind some of the world’s most revolutionary innovations and are not only comfortable in new and uncharted waters, we dive in headfirst. We are the original trailblazers that make the impossible possible; discovering new solutions to our customer’s toughest challenges.
Altair is an equal opportunity employer. Our backgrounds are diverse, and every member of our global team is critical to our success. Altair's history demonstrates a belief that empowering each individual authentic voice reinforces a culture that thrives because of the uniqueness among our team.

Title: Junior Systemutvecklare
Description:
Diadrom växer!
Nu söker vi fler systemutvecklare till vårta team och hoppas att du är just den vi söker! Vi erbjuder dig möjlighet att få arbeta i intressanta, komplexa och utmanande projekt tillsammans med engagerade kollegor.
Vi är en del av transformationen mot ett digitaliserat och mer hållbart samhälle. Innehållen i våra projekt drivs av teknikutveckling inom molnlösningar, mobila applikationer, elektrifierade produkter och av nya produktplattformar inom fordonsindustrin. Våra projekt omfattar områden som cyber security, data science, mjukvaruutveckling och drift av mjukvarusystem.

Arbetsuppgifter:
Vi arbetar främst med att stötta våra kunder i deras projekt och utvecklingsteam. Vi och våra kunder arbetar i Scrum/Agila team om ca 8 personer. Våra kunder finns främst inom fordonsbranschen. Våra medarbetare stannar vanligtvis på samma uppdrag i 2-5 år, beroende på komplexiteten i projektet, intresse och kompetensutveckling.

Hos oss får du möjlighet att utvecklas inom bl.a. programmering, fordonsdiagnostik, metodik för mjukvaruutveckling och du får tillgång till kurser och utbildningar och mentorskap från medarbetare.
Om detta låter spännande kommer du troligen att trivas hos oss.

Junior systemutvecklare är en person som har:
En B.Sc eller M.Sc inom datateknik, mekatronik, informationsteknik, mjukvaruutveckling eller relaterat tekniskt område
Kunskap och erfarenhet i ett eller flera programmeringsspråk, så som: C#, Java, Python, C, C++, JavaScript/TypeScript
Kunskap och erfarenhet av back-end eller full-stack utveckling
Körkort för personbil (eller på väg att ta)
Kunskap och erfarenhet av mjukvaruutvecklingsmetodik, APIer, databaser, Git
Förmågan och intresset att lösa problem
Intresse eller kunskaper inom områden såsom DevOps, Azure/AWS, containerization, Automatiserad testning, CI/CD, eller fordonsbranschen generellt är meriterande.
Hos oss är det även viktigt att du behärskar engelska flytande i både tal och skrift då detta krävs i kontakt med kollegor och kunder. Det är även meriterande om du talar svenska.

Vi kommer att lägga stor vikt vid din personlighet. Vi tror att du kommer att trivas och lyckas bäst i rollen om du skulle beskriva dig själv som:
Ansvarstagande för dina arbetsuppgifter och bidrar till teamet med din kunskap, lösningsförslag och frågeställningar
Att du trivs med att arbeta i agila team
Att du gillar att arbeta med senaste tekniken
En person som vill lära dig mer och få utveckla dina kunskaper
Vill lära dig fler kodspråk, tekniker och ramverk, verktyg och miljöer

3 anledningar till varför du ska börja på Diadrom
1. Vi har ett nischat fokus; Vi ser till att våra anställda är specialister på diagnostik. Vi kompletterar kundens projektgrupp med expertkunskap inom diagnostik, t.ex. centrala stödsystem, mjukvaruladdning, konfigurering eller off-boardverktyg, och lever upp till våra kunders förväntningar genom gedigen domänkunskap och fokus på att alltid leverera hög kvalitet.
2. Vi erbjuder dig möjligheten att få arbeta med intressanta och utmanande projekt tillsammans med erfarna och engagerade kollegor. Vi värnar om sammanhållning, hemmatillhörighet och månar om trivsel på företaget.
3. Vi har återkommande gemensamma aktiviteter och utbildningsdagar där alla ska känna att de är med och bidrar genom kunskapsspridning. Det är Du som gör det möjligt att Diadrom ständigt utvecklas!

Praktiskt om tjänsten
Omfattning: Heltid
Vi tillämpar fast månadslön och är kollektivavtalsanslutna
Företagsgemensam bonus (vinstdelning)
Friskvårdsbidrag och pensionssparande
Vi erbjuder sjukvårdsförsäkring
Jobbdator och mobil
Förmånsportal via Benify och möjlighet till personalbil


Sista ansökningsdag 15 januari. Intervjuer sker löpande.
För frågor kontakta Sandra eller Niclas, kontaktuppgifter finns nedan.

Följs oss på Instagram , Facebook och/eller LinkedIn för att få en bättre inblick i Diadroms värld och livet som Diadromare.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
About Assessio
Assessio is one of the largest Talent Assessment suppliers in the Nordics as well as in the Netherlands. As a SaaS company, we provide our services through internally developed SaaS platforms. We are 140 dedicated co-workers who share our vision of Zero Talent Waste.
We strive to contribute to an effective and fair labor market where everyone is assessed based on equal, relevant terms. Where potential is valued, and organizations find the talent they need.
Besides joining us on our journey to achieve our vision #Zerotalentwaste, we also offer a competitive remuneration package that includes excellent benefits, such as competitive salaries, a generous wellness allowance of SEK 5000 / year, and 6 weeks of vacation. In addition, participation in a bonus scheme, and the opportunity to work both within our centrally located Stockholm office and remotely for employees within Sweden.
Job Description

Our SaaS platform team develop and maintain the SaaS platforms that help our clients recruit and develop their workforce. As a Data Scientist at Assessio you will design, implement, and deploy robust prediction algorithms that give our customers completely new and unique insights. You will collaborate closely both with product owners and the whole engineering team. Assessio’s SaaS platform team comprises talented individuals with a broad range of cultural backgrounds. Your contribution will be essential to both the team and the business success of Assessio group. We are thus looking for a team player with a strong sense of commitment and responsibility, as well as excellent problem-solving skills.
Main Responsibilities
Research, design, implement, deploy and operate robust and scalable prediction algorithms with the target to give our clients completely new and unique insights
Design and implement pipelines and services for pre-processing, training, and serving of machine learning models and algorithms.
Communicate with stakeholders to understand & refine the business needs and targeted outcomes.
Working closely for the agile teams developing our new SaaS platform
Contribute to the definition and implementation of best practices in terms of data infrastructure and deployment pipelines.
Qualifications
B.Sc degree or higher in relevant engineering / data science field
Proficiency in a relevant programming language (e.g. Python as well as SQL)
Minimum 4 years of hands-on work experience in the Data Science field, preferably working with a range of machine learning approaches and algorithms.
Good knowledge and understanding of common predictive machine learning approaches and related performance metrics.
Deep understanding of predictive modelling, clustering and classification methods and algorithms.
Excellent problem-solving skills.
Good communication skills.
Good English skills (speaking and writing).
Beneficial to have:
Knowledge of trade-offs and considerations related to the application of machine learning and algorithms in social and health sciences.
Experience from working with cloud-based systems, particularly AWS, and its machine learning services.
Interest in data mesh and decentralised data architectures.
M.Sc. degree in the data science field.
Reporting
The Data Scientist is reporting to the CTO
Next step
Does this sound like the right job for you? Send us your application today!
The first step in the process will be to complete two tests: a problem-solving test (Matrigma) and a personality test (MAP). It will take you approximately 30 minutes – and we guarantee valuable feedback after the assessments and a quick response from our side. You will find more info about the process at our Career Site.
We look forward to getting in touch!
If you have any questions regarding the recruitment process, please contact Lydia Nöjd
– lydia.nojd@assessio.se

Title: Data Science Lead
Description:
Följ med på vår resa mot ett hållbart samhälle! SJ – Framtidens sätt att resa.
SJ är på en resa. En resa där målet är att bidra till ett hållbart samhälle genom att möjliggöra klimatsmart resande, i Sverige och i Norden. Vägen dit kantas av en mängd spännande möjligheter och utmaningar de kommande åren.
Vi växer och utvecklas inom hela verksamheten. Mångmiljardinvesteringar i nya moderna tåg, investeringar i digitala system för att effektivisera vår verksamhet, kompetensutveckling av vår personal, listan kan göras lång. Allt detta görs med kunden i fokus och med målet att göra det möjligt för fler att göra det hållbara resevalet.
Till huvudkontoret på Vasagatan 10 i Stockholm, söker vi nu en Data Science Lead som en grundläggande del i att etablera SJs Data & Analys-avdelning och genom det bidra till vår långsiktiga framgång.
I den här rollen är du ansvarig för att samla och utveckla SJ-koncernens Data Scientists genom att både själv driva djupgående initiativ liksom att organisera och stötta data science-arbetet tvärs koncernen. Organisatoriskt tillhör du SJ-koncernens centrala avdelning för Data & Analys och rapporterar till chefen för Data & Analys. Arbetet sker dels i nära samarbete med närmsta gruppen, dels med övriga på SJ som arbetar med avancerad/operationaliserad analys. Rollen är en av de första pusselbitarna som läggs för att skapa grunden till ett mer datadrivet SJ och avdelningen Data & Analys har som uppdrag att driva och guida koncernen framåt på den resan. Vi söker därför en driven och erfaren Data Scientist som kan leda i arbetet att låsa upp den outnyttjade potential som finns i våra omfattande datatillgångar.
Vem söker vi?
Vi söker dig med gedigen erfarenhet av avancerad/operationaliserad analys i komplexa och storskaliga miljöer tillsammans med god förmåga och intresse för att leda andra i en virtuell organisation. I botten har du akademisk examen inom matematiktung inriktning, exempelvis ingenjörsutbildning med fokus på matematik, statistik, datavetenskap, data science eller motsvarande. Du har erfarenhet av olika tekniska plattformar och programmeringsspråk och är väl insatt i hur samverkan med systemutvecklare, data engineers och kravställare kan och bör ske i en agil omgivning. Antagligen har du erfarenhet från en mogen kontext sett till förmåga att utvinna värde från data men har ett intresse för att själv vara med och bygga upp något liknande från grunden.
Du är självgående, nyfiken och ansvarstagande samt får energi av att växla mellan mer övergripande strukturella uppgifter och de som kräver en mer handfast och detaljerad insats.
Arbetsbeskrivning
Som Data Science Lead ansvarar du för att etablera, driva och utveckla samarbete i tvärfunktionellt community med de inom SJ som arbetar med data science-relaterade frågor. I detta ingår till en början att samla gruppen och fokusera dess medlemmar till gemensamma arbetssätt och verktyg för att sen tillsammans utforska nya möjligheter. Arbetet innebär även att bidra till den strategiska planen för hur SJs förmåga kopplat till data science ska utvecklas.
Arbetet bygger alltså på kontinuerlig dialog med koncernens alla delar och att identifiera och samla in utvecklingsbehov för att sedan prioritera dessa för genomförande. Du kommer att stödja andra och även driva egna utvecklingsinitiativ, vissa från grunden och andra genom att vidareutveckla och underhålla sedan tidigare framtagna lösningar.
Ambitionen är att på sikt utöka avdelningen Data & Analys med ytterligare Data Scientist-förmåga vilket då kommer innebära att uppgiften som Data Science Lead växer i form av ett arbetsledningsansvar.
Vad kan SJ erbjuda dig?
På SJ ger vi dig goda möjligheter och utrymme att påverka och bidra till utveckling. Det här är en utmanande och intressant roll som erbjuder frihet i kombination med stort ansvar. En roll som bidrar till, och möjliggör, ett hållbart resande. SJs utveckling och tillväxt har varit och förväntas långsiktigt att vara mycket god. Vår flexibilitet och förmåga att anpassa verksamheten till verkligheten har utvecklats till en av bolagets styrkor.
Kontakt
I den här rekryteringen samarbetar SJ med Jefferson Wells. För mer information om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Malin Magnusson 076-780 68 64.
Vi ser gärna att du skickar in din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast 15 feb.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
SJ vet att mångfald ger fler perspektiv och ökar SJs konkurrenskraft. Vi välkomnar därför sökanden med olika bakgrunder som vill vara med och bidra till ett inkluderande arbetsklimat.
SJ för människor närmare varandra, varje dag.
SJ är ett svenskt reseföretag som erbjuder hållbara tågresor i egen regi och i samarbete med andra. SJ är ett av Sveriges grönaste varumärken och en del av lösningen för att klimatmålen ska nås. Koncernens 5400 medarbetare i Sverige och Norge bidrar alla till ökat tågresande – framtidens sätt att resa.
Som marknadsledande tågoperatör knyter SJ ihop Sverige, Norge, liksom Skandinaviens huvudstäder och varje dag möts våra kunder och medarbetare på någon av våra 1500 avgångar från över 400 stationer. SJ ägs av svenska staten och har som uppdrag att driva lönsam persontrafik på järnväg.

Title: Open position summer job
Description:
Are you a student within IT, Project Management, Business or Data science and looking for a summer job within an innovative and tech-loving company?

We are looking for people who, like us, find product development together with creating customer value in an international market intriguing. Are you interested in bringing your ideas to the table and surround yourself with great co-workers? We use best in class technique, specialized expertise and our 20 years of experience striving to provide the market’s smartest field service solution. Digitalisation, technology and the need for sustainable development is rapidly changing the market. Our solutions contribute to higher quality and more efficient field service as well as a smarter energy systems, better work environment, less travels and yet a more mobile work force. Sounds interesting? Keep reading!

At isMobile you would be given the opportunity to try your wings and practice your theoretical knowledge within your field of study. For us it doesn't matter if you are in the first or last year of your studies. What we treasure is your personal attributes! "All about people" is one of our core values and central to everything we do. We strive to encourage employees to develop their skills as well as themselves. We want our people to grow with isMobile.

Having fun at work is also important for us. We have team-building activities such as kick-offs, training sessions outside the office, brainstorming sessions, jogging and skiing together.

If this sounds like a match for you, don't hesitate to apply!

Title: Team Manager till Insights & Data
Description:
Insights & Data är på en stark tillväxtresa och söker nu ytterligare en teamchef för att bidra till våra framgångar. Med en ny Hybrid & Flexible Work Policy arbetar vi tillsammans för att växa regionen med medarbetare i både Malmö och Helsingborg.
Om oss:
Insights & Data är marknadsledande inom Data, AI och Analytics och våra tjänster inkluderar konsultverksamhet inom bl.a. Analytics, Data Governance, Data Engineering, Data Science, AI & Machine Learning. Vi arbetar med såväl stora globala som mindre lokala kunder vilket ger våra konsulter en varierad arbetsdag och möjlighet till att ständigt utvecklas och lära nytt.
Insights & Data South har kontor i Malmö och i Helsingborg och består idag av sex konsultteam med närmare 100 medarbetare samt en lokal säljorganisation och ledningsgrupp. Vi samarbetar nära med våra kollegor på den svenska såväl som globala marknaden vilket ger oss kompetens och kapacitet att verkligen göra skillnad för våra kunder. Som teamchef i regionen kan du tillhöra antingen kontoret i Malmö eller i Helsingborg, men förväntas röra dig mellan kontoren vid behov. Du har även möjlighet att arbeta hemifrån som en del av vår Hybrid & Flexible Work Policy.
Om rollen:
Våra medarbetare är det viktigaste vi har och ett värderingsstyrt och empatisk ledarskap är viktigt för oss inom Insights & Data South. Då våra medarbetare arbetar hos kund, från våra lokala kontor såväl som hemifrån, ställer detta skifte stora krav på ett empatiskt, lyhört och närvarande ledarskap.
Vi arbetar ständigt med att vidareutveckla vår affär, vår personal och vårt erbjudande. Vi är resultatdrivna och arbetar tillsammans för att uppnå våra mål. Detta samtidigt som vi leder med hjärtat och ser till att våra medarbetare trivs, utvecklas och har roligt tillsammans. Vår lokala FUN committee hjälper oss att skapa trevliga stunder och vi har en tradition med Team Thursday då vi uppmanar våra konsulter att vara på kontoret, träffa sina kollegor och fika tillsammans.
Inclusion & Diversity är våra ledord och styrka - vår region består idag av medarbetare från hela världen med olika bakgrunder och erfarenheter såväl som olika åldrar, kön, sexualitet och religioner. För att lyckas i rollen och trivas väl i regionen tror vi att du har tidigare erfarenhet av att leda människor från olika kulturer och bakgrunder samt att du behärskar engelska i tal och skrift.
Vi tror att du som söker är initiativtagande och gillar att leda, driva och utveckla medarbetare såväl som oss som företag. Du uppskattar ett kreativt arbetsklimat med internationella kontaktytor. Som person är du självgående, strukturerad, driven, engagerad och lösningsorienterad.
I rollen ingår:
Formellt personalansvar för team på mellan 15-25 personer
Rekrytering till ditt team
Hjälpa och coacha konsulterna i sin karriär- och kompetensutveckling
Verksamhetsutveckling och ledningsarbete
Samarbete med övriga teamchefer, säljorganisation, leveransansvariga och stödfunktioner för att nå budget, finansiella resultat och mätetal inom medarbetarnöjdhet
Du sitter i regionens ledningsgrupp och blir en viktig del i det operativa ledningsarbetet och affärsplaneringen. Du rapporterar till vår regionchef / Head of South; Malin Unger.
Rollen innebär 50% arbete som Team Manager och 50% arbete i konsultuppdrag i linje med din kompetens
Vi söker dig med:
Tidigare erfarenhet inom ledarskap, gärna från konsultverksamhet
Genuint intresse för människor där du brinner för att utveckla andra såväl som dig själv
Relevant högskoleexamen eller motsvarande erfarenhet
... och gärna erfarenhet av / att du behärskar:
Bakgrund inom något av våra fokusområden (Data, analytics & AI)
Svenska i tal och skrift
Ansökan
Urval sker löpande, men skicka in din ansökan redan idag, och senast den 2022-02-28
Tillsättning sker snarast.
Har du frågor eller funderingar kontakta gärna Anna Karlsson, Insights & Data Recruitment - anna.karlsson@capgemini.com
Vi ser fram emot att ta emot din ansökan!

Title: Data Scientist Manager
Description:
We believe that our future success will be based on our ability to leverage the large amounts of data generated on our platform every day. We need the ability to gain fast insights from usage of our services to enable short cycles of product refinement and be able to develop new data-driven services based on all of our data.
During 2020 we began migrating our backend services to the Google Cloud Platform (GCP) with the ambition of being one of the few banks with cloud-based services in a highly regulated industry. During 2021 we started to build our next generation data & analytics environment on top of that and also on GCP.
This year we will focus more on personalisation and develop the capabilities we need to be able to use data-driven services to personalise the customer experience and contribute to other strategic goals.
About the role
As a Data Scientist Manager your focus will be to develop, implement and maintain different types of data-driven services together with other Data scientists and development teams, as well as lead Data scientists and Data analysts.
This role is part of Data & Insights at Nordnet, consisting of data engineering, business intelligence and data science competence responsible for the new environment, spanning from data pipelines to dashboards to data-driven services as well as data analysts supporting the organisation with insights in the daily work. The Data scientists and Data analysts are integrated in other development teams to ensure that we understand the customer needs and develop the best data-driven services and insights.
As Data Science Manager you are responsible for the outcome of your teams, and you use coaching, facilitation and your practical experience to help your teams grow, succeed and continuously deliver value. You are also responsible for hiring, staffing and onboarding.
About you
You are passionate about data, leadership and want to contribute with your experience and knowledge when we take our next steps in developing data-services and supporting the organisation with insights.
As a Data Scientist Manager we believe that this is you
Experience from Machine Learning frameworks and developing end-to-end projects in production.
Experience from working in GCP
Strong communication skills and have the ability to engage both technical and non-technical stakeholders in our vision
An empathic leader, willing to share your knowledge and mentoring and coaching others.
Experience of driving change in an organisation
Good understanding of data engineering practices and data modelling
Bank and Finance experience
Hold a BA degree or equivalent in engineering, computational or technical subject.
What we offer
Nordnet started from a passionate belief that changing the hierarchical financial world was possible. We became part of redefining the industry when we gave the customers power over their own savings. You will become part of a journey that has only yet started towards the vision of making our customers the best investors they can be. To be leading in IT is pivotal for that journey and you will work with colleagues who have a great passion for that goal.
We are 800 employees in Stockholm, Oslo, Helsinki and Copenhagen. We cooperate, exchange ideas and use our core competencies in order to continuously improve the way we meet our customers. Open communication, creativity and engagement are important parts of our everyday life at the office.
Visit us on www.nordnetab.com,www.nordnet.se,
www.nordnet.no, www.nordnet.dk_ and _www.nordnet.fi.
Application
We will start interviewing immediately. Please note that we do only accept applications through our recruitment system, hence no email applications will be considered.
If you have questions, please contact Talent Acqusition Partner Alva Hellberg at alva.hellberg@nordnet.se
We want to inform you that Nordnet conducts credit and background checks on the final candidate.
We look forward to receiving your application!
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Product Analyst
Description:
Tink was founded in 2012, and a decade later became part of Visa in 2022. Tink was created with the aim of changing the banking industry for the better. We have built Europe’s most robust open banking platform – with the broadest, deepest connectivity and powerful services that create value out of the financial data. We offer the tools that allow anyone – from big banks and fintechs to startups – to build the future of financial services across Europe.
How you'll be part of changing an industry
As more and more customers and developers onboard with Tink, it is our job to ensure their experience is awesome. We believe that “That which is measured, improves” and in the world of modern data science and analytics, the measurement itself is a fundamental part of the improvement process.

We’re in the midst of building a world-class data platform and analytics team, used to fuel our product development with reporting, insights and testing frameworks. Joining Tink as a product analyst now means you’ll be a part of both building and shaping the future of insight work, at a leading fintech player.

What we look for
We’re looking for someone who will help Tink reach the forefront of data-informed, and driven, decision making. We look for that “we’re in this together” attitude, and an ambition to get your hands dirty and do things right, to balance the short-term and setting us up for the future. You enjoy working with a wide range of tasks. Everything from deeper technical work, for example building data pipelines and setting up dashboards, to working with insight generation and collaborating with product managers on more high level objectives.
With that, we think you’ve already spent a couple of years learning the tools of analytics and have sharpened your soft skills working with, and influencing, stakeholders and business leaders. You’ve probably worked in a product-oriented company, ideally in the financial sector, but hey - if you haven't, you can learn.

Day-to-day:
You’ll work with pretty much every function at Tink, to bring an understanding of how our products are performing, what we do well, and what we can do better. Our Data Foundations team will provide you with great help to build a modern platform for data collection, transformations and pipelines. The team’s responsibilities stretch wide and we’ll always be split between instrumenting data, automating reporting and driving analytics projects where we deep-dive in some aspect of our product.
In the short term, we collaborate with Product Managers and engineering squads to make sure we collect high-quality fundamental data. It also includes making basic metrics from that data accessible to those same stakeholders. Be it either through dashboards, or empowering people to query themselves. Empowering people is an important aspect of the role. You will be educating our stakeholders how to interpret and work with our data.
In the medium and longer-term, a significant share of reporting is automated and focus shifts more towards understanding what drives performance, deep-dive problems and opportunities, and develop our capabilities for advanced analytics, A/B-testing, and data-driven design.

Required qualifications
Minimum one year of experience in a similar role, perhaps you picked up the skills in a different area or over a different timeframe - let’s talk!
Supporting analytics projects and initiatives from inception to delivery.
Good communication skills and collaborating efficiently with stakeholders.
Hands-on work with basic SQL, metrics reporting and building dashboards/business-intelligence.
An understanding of analytical & statistical methods, e.g. hypothesis testing, AB-tests, regression modeling and similar.
Scripting experience in R or Python’s data libraries (or Julia or Matlab or SPSS or something else).


Don't hesitate to contact us for further information or questions you might have.

We're looking forward to your application!

Who we are at Tink
We are a company of developers and engineers – it’s in our DNA to imagine, build and iterate. We were founded with a vision of transforming an industry that lacked competition and momentum. And we have built a company of passionate over-achievers who all believe there is always a better way of doing things.
People from all over Europe – and the world – have joined us on our mission to build the biggest and best open banking platform in Europe.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Founded in 2018, Kreditz is already the market leader in PSD2-credit scoring products.
We use Open Banking/PSD2-technology to create our revolutionizing real-time credit scoring products, which are beloved by banks, financial institutions, iGaming companies and many more. Kreditz products enable consumers, and businesses, to gain financial inclusion, and financial opportunity where none would be available with traditional credit scoring systems.
Our long-term vision "One world, One score" translates into our everyday mission of financial inclusion, and financial opportunity, for everyone around the globe
– Everyone deserves a fair assessment.
Come join us on our impactful mission!

ABOUT THE POSITION
Thanks to 18 months of unbroken growth (+310% FY21 vs FY20) we are now looking to increase our analytics organization further with an awesome Data Science ‘magician’ eager to advance Kreditz revolutionizing products even further alongside a team of credit scoring experts, mathematicians and genuinely passionate colleagues.
We are currently entering an exciting phase (startup>scaleup) where we will expand our market presence further, from the Nordics to selected countries in Europe. Our clients range from some of Europe’s largest banks and iGaming companies to smaller, innovative businesses.
As a Data Scientist at Kreditz, your playing field is data, vast amount of data. Our products and services are highly data driven, and to remain innovative you need to be confident in the analysis of both the known, and the unknown. Kreditz expects you to be able to analyze large internal and external data sets, make data driven conclusions, and evaluate your findings to optimize Kreditz algorithms and statistical models. This role is an important part of Kreditz growing analytics team, which is led by our CAO.
If you share the excitement to work with state-of-the-art technology within Open Banking/PSD2, and to deliver market leading solutions that make a positive impact on our society, all the while being part of a growth journey across the world – this is the right position for you!

WHAT CAN KREDITZ OFFER
One-way ticket to an amazing growth journey you will never forget – A journey where everyone in the team plays a central role for our company’s success
Fun-loving, passionate, and talented colleagues with whom to share small and big, company and personal, milestones and accomplishments
Humble corporate culture – we celebrate all wins, no matter the size, together
24/7 access to gym/sauna/sports center at our office PLUS additional wellness allowance

TASKS
Some of the tasks you will be performing as Data Scientist at Kreditz:
Management and structuring of vast amounts of data
Analysis, interpretations and predictions of data
Transaction categorization and exploration (NLP, classification)
Optimization of Kreditz algorithms and statistical models
Model development, follow ups and evaluation
Advancement and implementation of DL and ML models
Project lead and participation for client projects
Proactive data driven product development together with Product owner

WE ARE LOOKING FOR
A colleague who is analytical, structured and communicative. Someone who (like us) is up for the BIG challenge to disrupt traditional credit scoring systems via Open Banking/PSD2-technology. To be successful in this role, you must have a positive
“We can do it” mindset, along with an appreciation of working in a fast-paced growth company. You are comfortable in being independent in your daily work as well as acting with responsibility both towards your colleagues and clients.
Additionally, we believe that you have:
+2 yrs experience from financial services/tech/insurance/consulting or equivalent relevant experience
A relevant academic background (Engineering, Data/IT, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics)
Some experience from DL/ML/NPL projects within relevant industry
Confident in coding languages such as: Python, R and SQL
Very good communications-, and presentation-, skills in English (speech/writing), Swedish or other language skills is meritorious
Credit risk modeling from bank or financial institutions is meritorious
Experience from PSD2/Open Banking is meritorious

APPOINTMENT OF ROLE
Q4 2022
SCOPE
Full time, permanent employment (tillsvidareanställning)
SALARY
Fixed monthly salary
REPORTING
You will be reporting to the company's CAO
WORKPLACE
Our office is in Danderyd, Stockholm.
RECRUITMENT PROCESS
We interview candidates on an ongoing basis (ongoing selection)

CONTACT
Lorenzo Puccio, COO, lorenzo@kreditz.com
If you want to know more about the role, feel free to reach out to Magnus Källhager, Chief Analytics Officer, magnus@kreditz.com , +4670-7913984

Title: Junior Data Engineer
Description:
Substorm is a consulting and development company in the field of Intelligent Automation. We create customer value in the Digitization area through change management and technology development. We offer understandable solutions and create data-driven insights with the help of techniques from AI / machine learning, RPA and Business Intelligence. We also conduct research activities within Agenda 2030's global goals for sustainable development, specifically No. 5 Gender equality and No. 9 Sustainable industry, innovations and infrastructure.

We have offices across Sweden, from Luleå in the North to Stockholm and Gothenburg in the South - and we want to grow!

We are now looking for Junior Data Engineers to join our fantastic team!

You will work with data processing and data warehousing and help build our infrastructure for use both as stand-alone services and as part of bigger Machine Learning projects. You will be part of implementing the architecture enabling our data science projects, our business reporting requirements and our visualization needs.
We believe that you have a university degree in data engineering, computer science, machine learning or other relevant fields, or have proven experience achieved by other means. We also believe that you have:
Familiarity with ETL/ELT, SQL and SQL transformations
Familiarity with basic concepts and mechanics of traditional databases, data warehouses and other advanced data structures
Familiarity working with cloud based platforms
An agile mindset and know and care about a CI/CD way of working


As a person, you are enterprising, solution-oriented and caring. You can explain business value and benefits with your ideas and solutions in a professional way, and you are happy to convey your knowledge to both customers and colleagues. You are a true team player and are always ready for learning new technologies and skills.
Our company is growing fast and offer great opportunities for learning and variety in your work.
Candidates are expected to hold a valid work permit for the EU and Sweden.
More about Substorm
Substorm consists of developers, business analysts as well as automation strategists. We organize our work based on the customer’s need but preferably we deliver as a team. Technology is in our backbone, but we always adjust to our customers actual need. Our day to day work is fast-paced and exciting with a lot of heart and engagement. Conferences overseas, after works and other more or less spontaneous events spices up our work - and we have a lot of fun together!

Title: Software Developer - Data Engineer
Description:
Centiro is a tech company that connects, empowers, and makes delivery networks available and smarter for marquee brands and market leaders. Centiro is a fast grower with 500+ colleagues in 8 countries. All types of goods get delivered on time in over 175 countries thanks to Centiro technology. Centiro has created a human centric and award-winning culture and believes businesses are a key driving force in striving towards a sustainable future. Centiro exists to be part of the solution for better commerce and a better world. Founded in 1998, with offices in Sweden, India, Spain, Canada, the UK, and the US. Read more at centiro.com

Get to know more of our colleagues and hear about who they are, their roles, and how it is to be at Centiro. Meet them here.

About the role
Working at Centiro is different. Inspiring, challenging and rewarding. We are on a clear and rapid path of global expansion and are looking for talents with a passion and drive to make a difference. This is an exciting time to be joining the team and be a part of something special.

Centiro’s Software Developers create the next generation technologies for Centiro’s Supply Chain Network Cloud, crucial in the world of digital trade and e-commerce. As a Software Developer in our platform team your everyday work will be to develop our internal data science and machine learning platform based on Google Cloud Platform.
You will work in a team together with other Software Developers and Application Specialists. Our teams consist of individuals with varied skills who solves the complete assignment, from analysis, design and development to test and integration.
You will develop, form and support our platform and architecture based on GCP enabling our data science initiatives within logistics and transport management.

Who you are
You are a team player who understands the importance of cooperation and helping each other. A collaborative mindset and attitude are more important than prestige and personal priorities. With all tasks, everyone is equal in helping each other succeed.
You are expected to try, test and learn. You are encouraged to seize opportunities and continuously develop with Centiro’s robust confidence in your ability. You are spurred by continuous improvements and seeing things from a new perspective.

Competences & Skills
Kotlin
Python
Apache Beam
SQL


Nice but not needed

Knowledge C#/.NET
Apache Airflow
Terraform
A few years of experience from the industry
Education in software development. Either from university, polytechnic or equivalent

What we Offer
Centiro is a trailblazing tech company in our industry. We were awarded Sweden’s no 1 Workplace by Great Place to Work 2021! Using the latest technology, you get to work with world leading brands in an organization without bosses, with self-governing teams, where you’re not only allowed, but expected, to try test and learn.
Our top-modern, sustainable and thoughtfully designed Global Hub is located in Viared, Borås. Fancy a visit to the gym, a coffee at the roof-top patio or ping-pong? Or maybe a game of Mario Kart or try out our Padel court? Centiro’s philosophy is to embrace balance in life – we call it Life-Life Balance. We offer generous terms for wellness, healthcare, salary and pension. And, of course, you’ll be part of a wonderful team of colleagues!
Welcome to apply today!

Best in class
Sustainability and security are essential at Centiro. We achieved the gold level in the assessment of environmental, social, and ethical performance performed by EcoVadis; Gold Rating, Top 1%. We are above and beyond standards. We not only follow them, we develop them.
At Centiro we celebrate difference. We strongly believe that diversity of background, experience, and perspectives are integral for a dynamic workplace for our colleagues and a successful collaboration with our customers.

Title: Junior Data Engineer
Description:
Job ID: 1341
Location: Stockholm, Sweden
Stockholm or Helsinki | Hybrid | Full-time
__
As a data engineer at Bonava you will build data pipelines and write code to transfer, transform and prepare data for various data services at the company. You will enable the business to utilise the data for insights and help us as a company to become more data driven.
The role
In this role you will design, build, and maintain data pipelines in Microsoft Synapse Analytics. You will write code in PySpark (a mix between Python and SQL that runs on Spark) to update, transform, and store data automatically in efficient ways in our data lake. You will also build algorithms to extract, create and transform data that will be used to deliver new insights to the business.
The way we work
The team you will be joining is a distributed team split between Stockholm and Helsinki. As the Data Science-team we cover everything from integrations to reporting and AI. We use a hybrid setup, mixing remote work with working from the office.
We work in an agile way aiming for small frequent releases using guiding principles from the software development world. Our tech stack is mostly within Microsoft Azure, where we are using PySpark and Synapse Analytics heavily. For reporting we use Microsoft Power BI.
Who we are looking for
For this role you need to enjoy writing and optimizing code as well as digging into data flows and integrations. You learn new technical tools quickly when you have the proper support. Working independently is something you are used to, but you are also comfortable with asking for help and helping your colleagues when needed. You have a high attention to details, and you understand the importance of both correctness in the data and the code as well as prioritisation.
We believe you have a MSc in computer science, data science or information systems, or a similar type of education.
Required
Knowledge of relational databases, modelling of data and normalisation of data structures
Experience in coding in some SQL-dialect
Experience coding in Python
Knowledge of complexity, optimisation, and characteristics of less and more efficient algorithms
Proficient level in English
You can fulfil these requirements through your education or through work experience.
Meriting
It is also meriting if you have experience of any of the following:
Git in some form for version control
Azure, AWS or GCP
Azure Synapse Analytics or Azure Data Factory
Spark and especially PySpark
AI, machine learning or advanced analytics
CI/CD
Join our journey
When you apply, please submit your resume and cover letter in English together with grade transcripts from your higher education. We are reviewing applications continuously, so please send your application as soon as possible but no later than the 12th of February.
If you have any specific questions, please contact Helena Sjöberg at helena.sjoberg@bonava.com, the recruiting manager.
This is Bonava
Bonava is a leading residential developer in Northern Europe that creates homes and neighbourhoods where people have the highest quality of life. The company is the first residential developer in Europe to receive approval from the Science Based Targets initiative for its climate targets. With its 2,100 co-workers, Bonava develops residential housing in Germany, Sweden, Finland, Norway, Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania. Bonava’s shares and green bond are listed on Nasdaq Stockholm.
We are changing the housing game
Join our journey
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Marketing Project Manager
Description:
Marketing Project Manager

THE OPPORTUNITY
To our growing Commercial Department we are looking for a Marketing Project Manager to bridge between various stakeholders and teams in the Commercial department. The Marketing Project Manager will be managing, steering, and implementing creative concepts and other larger projects that are driven by the Brand and Visual Communication department.

The job is to create an overview of incoming tasks, filter, prioritize and plan them. Thereafter, through a well defined creative process, in close collaboration with various stakeholders, ensure that the projects are on time and aligned. You will together with the Head of Brand & Campaigns and Art Directors secure that the project is on concept and on brand.

We are running big campaigns with many placements in a complex structure which requires that you are used to driving the whole process, from start to finish and from top to bottom. Making sure that the process of the project is structured, time efficient, as well as optimized by providing service to all the stakeholders involved.

We are looking for a business minded and communicative person with a passion for communication, ecommerce and has a strong commercial side. Does this sound interesting? Then this might be the perfect opportunity!

WHAT YOU WILL DO
Filter, prioritize, plan and lead tasks and projects ~ A-Z and top to bottom.
Keep project overview for all stakeholders.
Secure deliveries and alignment within the creative process.
Work in Jira.
Be proactive, able to manage sudden changes and handle many stakeholders.

YOUR PROFILE
As a person we believe that you are used to taking full responsibility and driving the projects from start to finish. You are used to communicating and collaborating with different stakeholders throughout the business, from Art Directors to Marketing executives.

Min. 3-5 years of experience from a similar role.
Project Management experience preferably from advertising or marketing.
Experienced in working with the same stakeholders over time and building long term relations.
Fluent in English, both orally and written.
Strong proactive communication skills, entrepreneurial approach, ability to function in a fast-paced environment and ability to collaborate in a team environment.
Proficient skills in Jira .

Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.

Welcome to apply for the position!
BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.

Title: Passionate Statistician for Data Sciences & Quantitative Biology
Description:
Are you a curious and driven Statistician or Data Scientist? Would you like to join us on our journey where your unique statistical and quantitative skills will have a profound impact on R&D? If yes, this position at AstraZeneca might be your next challenge!

We have an exciting opportunity to join our Data Sciences & Quantitative Biology department as a Senior Statistician based at AstraZeneca in Gothenburg, Sweden. The team is made up of passionate statisticians, bioinformaticians, machine learning specialists and image analysts. We are part of the Discovery Sciences function that applies deep technical expertise in specialist technologies to support the delivery of targets and molecules to the early AstraZeneca pipeline. We work collaboratively towards a common goal, pushing the boundaries of science, by applying our quantitative skills to complex biological problems to deliver new medicines to patients.

Learn more about our Data Sciences & Quantitative Biology department here: https://pages.beamery.com/astrazeneca/page/quantitativebiology or watch our DS & QuBi film to get to know the team better: A Life-changing day - Meet our Quantitative Biology team at AstraZeneca

What you will do:
You will play an important role in our greater organisation by applying your statistical knowledge to drug discovery projects in a variety of collaborative project teams.

As a Senior Statistician you will work with a problem-solving attitude and a perceptive approach to:
Identify and deliver solutions to address key biological questions using quantitative approaches
Build and internalize appropriate algorithms and techniques to answer biological questions
Develop and implement statistical learning models
Contribute to and lead projects
Engage with external collaborators via publications and presentations

Essential in the role:
We believe that your focus is set on solving challenging biological problems through partnerships. You are a specialist in your field, and you know that the best results are achieved by utilizing the strengths of every individual.

You should also have:
Great interpersonal skills and be an agile communicator that can explain complex statistical methods to scientists with different levels of statistical knowledge.
Experience in data analysis and knowledge of some of the following areas: experimental design, linear/nonlinear models, Bayesian methods, statistical learning/AI and modelling.
Programming experience with tools such as R, Shiny, Julia, Stan or similar.
PhD or equivalent in statistics, mathematics, data science or similar.

To be successful in this role, you enjoy operating in a multi-disciplinary research environment. You like teamwork, have a collaborative nature and will be an encouraging colleague to all.

Why AstraZeneca?
Thrive in a place where the brightest and most curious minds seamlessly come together in our inclusive environment. Here we are committed to making a difference in patients’ lives. We have built our business around our passion for science, and now we are fusing data and technology with the latest scientific innovations to achieve the next wave of breakthroughs.

So, what’s next? If you want to be a part of pushing the boundaries of science together with us - apply today!

We look forward to learning more about you. Please send in your application as soon as possible - but no later than 26th February, 2023.

For more information about the position please contact the hiring manager Peter Konings, peter.konings@astrazeneca.com.

Additional information:
Our Gothenburg site: https://www.astrazeneca.com/our-science/gothenburg.html
Life in Gothenburg: https://www.movetogothenburg.com/
AstraZeneca R&D: https://www.astrazeneca.com/r-d.html

Title: Performance Marketing Specialist
Description:
Performance Marketing Specialist
THE OPPORTUNITY
Booztlet is expanding its marketing team and is on an ambitious growth journey in the upcoming years. Now we are looking for a Performance Marketing Specialist to join the team and support our growth across Europe.
As a Performance Marketing Specialist, you will be responsible for activities that will build Booztlet’s presence on performance channels – Google Ads, Social, Display, Video, and other similar activities. You will play an essential part in growing the business and making sure we deliver on our goals.
You will be a part of a lean organization focused on execution and driving growth. Together we develop a solid foundation that lifts our ambitious goals forward, and to a new level.
Short decision-making where the right person will be able to provide a lot of value and play a vital part in the marketing team. Booztlet is a platform for development and open mindset toward new initiatives and ideas.
This is a fantastic opportunity to join a growing interesting team and take your career to the next level.

To be successful in this role, you have a keen interest in data and a good understanding and knowledge of the market and e-commerce practices. You are an ambitious doer with strong analytical skills and a structured way of working. You are a self-driven team player with good time management skills.
1-2 years of work experience in a similar role
Experience working with Google Ads (shopping + text ads) and Facebook Ads
Experience with data feeds
Previous experience in e-commerce or digital product marketing

Fluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered)
Please apply for this position as soon as possible as we work with ongoing selection and interviews. The first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal-opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Data Analyst
Description:
Do you want to be a part of a new Analytics Operations team and get to work in an inspiring environment? Then you should keep reading!
DevPort are now looking for a Data Analyst to join our clients new Analytics Operations team. The Analytics Operations team should act as a catalyst and take responsibility for analytics value creation in all phases; from early ideation with stakeholders to creating runtime dashboards and data pipelines or guiding superusers to help them create their own dashboards. We also cooperate with Data Scientists and Data Engineers to run AI/ML models in operations. The Analytics Operations team is new and as such you will be part of developing the unit and creating successful use cases.
Our clients new Data, Analytics & AI organization is focused on unleashing the value of data collected from connected customer assets. The team are set out to drive the transformation into a data driven culture, where Data, Analytics & AI/ML are an integral part in their services and internal processes. By spanning across Data Foundation, Data Analytics and Data Science they can provide their stakeholders with actionable insights and take ownership of the whole process from ideation and exploration to analytics operations.

About the role
Drive the data journey by connecting with stakeholders, running workshops, identify opportunities and take it from idea to value.
Develop state-of-the art solutions, dashboards, and insight reports.
Stay at the forefront in the analytics space and share knowledge and experience with colleagues.

Your profile
You have a degree in a relevant field or practical experience from utilizing data to drive change.
You are a creative, entrepreneurial problem-solver with an inquisitive attitude and are not afraid of complex challenges or unconventional approaches.
You routinely use dashboarding as a tool for problem solving, and are experienced in at least one dashboarding solution (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik, Tableau, QuickSight, Grafana).
You confidently and systematically build analysis approaches from scratch, including data extraction, scripting and/or programming in relevant languages and analysis with creation of informative and appealing visualizations.
You are a communicative person that builds and maintains trust with stakeholders and colleagues.
Humorous; because, in the end, working in the team should be fun.

What can we offer you?
You will be part of a highly skilled analytics team that together with our stakeholders creates great value in short- and long-term engagements. In this team you will be able to make a data-driven impact on sustainable transport solutions for our client, their customers and society at large - and have fun while doing it. Your workplace will be based in Lindholmen in Gothenburg.

Application
Apply by following the steps below. If you have any questions regarding the position, send an email to Elin Thulin at elin.thulin@devport.se
I am looking forward to read you application!

About DevPort
DevPort is a technology consulting company in an expansive development phase with headquarter in Gothenburg and offices in Stockholm, Linköping, Helsingborg and Karlskrona. DevPort has its core competence in the automotive industry and employs more than 500 people in three business areas - Digital solutions, production development and product development.
We are proud of our employees and of collaborating with several of the world's leading vehicle manufacturers, companies in the defense industry and other development-intensive industries.
We are characterized by a family culture with entrepreneurship, competence, security and a community that infuses the company's operations and contributes to a pleasant and inspiring workplace.

Title: Sr Clinical Data Scientist
Description:
Description
Senior Clinical Data Scientist
Syneos Health is the only fully integrated biopharmaceutical solutions organization purpose-built to accelerate customer success. We lead with a product development mindset, seamlessly connecting our capabilities to add high-value insights to speed therapies to patients and provide practical value to help our customers achieve their objectives.
Our Clinical Development model brings the customer and the patient to the center of everything that we do. We are continuously looking for ways to simplify and streamline our work to not only make Syneos Health easier to work with, but to make us easier to work for.
Whether you join us in a Functional Service Provider partnership or a Full-Service environment, you’ll collaborate with passionate problem solvers, innovating as a team to help our customers achieve their goals. We are agile and driven to accelerate the delivery of therapies, because we are passionate to change lives.
Discover what our 29,000 employees, across 110 countries already know:
WORK HERE MATTERS EVERYWHERE
Why Syneos Health
We are passionate about developing our people, through career development and progression; supportive and engaged line management; technical and therapeutic area training; peer recognition and total rewards program.
We are committed to our Total Self culture – where you can authentically be yourself. Our Total Self culture is what unites us globally, and we are dedicated to taking care of our people.
We are continuously building the company we all want to work for and our customers want to work with. Why? Because when we bring together diversity of thoughts, backgrounds, cultures, and perspectives – we’re able to create a place where everyone feels like they belong.
Job responsibilities
Serves as Functional Lead for Clinical Data Science including primary contact for internal liaison between Clinical Data Science and Project Management, Clinical Monitoring, and other functional groups
Acts as central steward of clinical data quality, monitors risks through the holistic review of clinical and operational data, using high level knowledge of the protocol, taking into account the specific therapeutic area aspects of the protocol related to the data collected and aligning with cross functional operational plans to drive comprehensive clinical data quality
Ensures the required data elements and corresponding data quality oversight steps are identified to support the defined study analysis
Works with assigned project teams to communicate, address, troubleshoot and resolve data related questions and recommends potential solutions; escalates issues which potentially impact patient safety and study analysis
Coordinates cross functional data cleaning activities to ensure quality standards and timelines are met for clinical data deliverables Ensures the required data elements and corresponding data quality oversight steps are identified to support the defined project analysis
Drives the development of the clinical data acquisition plan and corresponding data flow diagram with the study team, assess risks associated with protocol design, study set parameters that could impact the credibility and reliability of the trial results, aligns data flow with the study protocol to ensure data collected meets regulatory and study endpoint requirements.
Drives the development of analytical tools, utilizes analytical platform/dashboard to detect potentially unreliable data that may impact the validity of the trial results Performs analytic reviews as defined in scope of work and data acquisition plan, identifies root cause to systematically resolve data issues
Monitors and communicates project progress to the Sponsor and project team including use of project status reports and tracking tools/metrics
Ensures launch, delivery and completion of all Clinical Data Sciences activities and milestones according to contractual agreement and relevant Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), guidelines, and regulations
Review, maintain budget and identify out of scope for Clinical Sciences activities, raise to PM to be implemented in required change order
Plans, manages, and requests Clinical Data Science resources for assigned projects
Coordinates the work of the assigned Clinical Data Science team
Develops and maintains project plans, specifications, and documentation in line with SOP requirements
Maintains documentation on an ongoing basis and ensures that all TMF filing is up to date for necessary files
Participates in, and presents at internal, Sponsor, third-party, and investigator meetings on behalf of clinical data science responsibilities
Prepares input, and participates in proposal bid defense meetings and request for proposals on behalf of clinical data science responsibilities
Plans for and creates necessary documentation to support internal and external audits; participates in such audits on behalf of clinical data sciences responsibilities
Trains and mentors new or junior team members
Maintains proficiency in Clinical Data Science systems and processes through regular training. May attend/represent the company at professional meetings/conferences
Performs other work-related duties as assigned. Minimal travel may be required (up to 25%)
Qualifications
What we’re looking for
BA/BS in the biological sciences, computer sciences, mathematics, or data sciences and/or related disciplines in the natural science/health care space. MS degree is preferred. In lieu of degree, equivalent relevant work experience
Clinical Data Science experience or an equivalent combination of education and experience
Experience in Clinical Data Science practices and relational database management software systems
Strong knowledge of the drug development process and its impact on data quality, in particular risk-based approach, biometrics procedures, workflows.
Aptitude for understanding analytic modeling methods such as regression, classification and clustering
Strong project management skills and knowledge of project management methodologies
Strong analytical skills and knowledge of Artificial intelligence /machine learning methodologies preferred
Demonstrated staff leadership skills
Knowledge of ALCOA++ data quality principles
Strong experience with protocol interpretation, data collection and data cleaning specification development
Experienced with data analysis/data review and visualization tool sets including but not limited to Python, R, Spotfire, SAS
Knowledge of medical terminology, clinical data, and ICH/GCP regulatory requirements for clinical studies, in particular requirements applicable to Clinical Data Sciences
Proficiency in MS Windows navigation, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and email applications
Effective oral and written communication and presentation skills
Good organizational, planning, and time management skills with the ability to multitask under tight deadlines while providing attention to detail
Ability to be flexible and adapt to change, to work independently, as well as part of a multi-disciplinary team
Ability to make effective decisions and manage multiple priorities in a highly dynamic environment
Get to know Syneos Health
Over the past 5 years, we have worked with 94% of all Novel FDA Approved Drugs, 95% of EMA Authorized Products and over 200 Studies across 73,000 Sites and 675,000+ Trial patients.
No matter what your role is, you’ll take the initiative and challenge the status quo with us in a highly competitive and ever-changing environment. Learn more about Syneos Health.
Additional Information:
Tasks, duties, and responsibilities as listed in this job description are not exhaustive. The Company, at its sole discretion and with no prior notice, may assign other tasks, duties, and job responsibilities. Equivalent experience, skills, and/or education will also be considered so qualifications of incumbents may differ from those listed in the Job Description. The Company, at its sole discretion, will determine what constitutes as equivalent to the qualifications described above. Further, nothing contained herein should be construed to create an employment contract. Occasionally, required skills/experiences for jobs are expressed in brief terms. Any language contained herein is intended to fully comply with all obligations imposed by the legislation of each country in which it operates, including the implementation of the EU Equality Directive, in relation to the recruitment and employment of its employees. The Company is committed to compliance with the Americans with Disabilities Act, including the provision of reasonable accommodations, when appropriate, to assist employees or applicants to perform the essential functions of the job.

Title: Dataanalytiker/Data scientist
Description:
Vill du arbeta med dataanalys och data science?
Nu letar vi efter dig som vill arbeta på koncernens utvecklingsavdelning som dataanalytiker och/eller data scientist i vårt Business Intelligence-team. Du kommer där att bidra aktivt till koncernens vision att bli ”världens mest resurseffektiva region” genom att stärka vår datadrivna beslutsförmåga. Vi är på god väg och behöver ytterligare vässa vår affärsintelligens. Med hjälp av rapporter, statistik och nyckeltal bidrar du till att teamet levererar rätt data, till rätt person och i rätt tid. Beroende på profil använder du även AI för att skapa kreativa och värdefulla lösningar utifrån vår stora datamängd.
Dina arbetsuppgifter:
Arbeta nära verksamheten med att förstå behov och önskemål.
Ta fram BI-rapporter för beslutsstöd och analyser som stöttar våra affärsområden i deras dagliga verksamhet.
Driva arbetet med att samla in och förädla data från våra olika system.
Utforska nya affärsmöjligheter i vår stora datamängd genom nya tekniker som AI och Machine Learning.
Du som person är nyfiken, positiv och prestigelös. I teamet skapar du engagemang genom att vara engagerad och social. Du bidrar med initiativ och kreativa lösningar, samtidigt som du är ansvarstagande och kvalitetsmedveten i ditt sätt att arbeta.
Erfarenheter du tar med till oss:
Universitets- eller högskoleutbildning inom minst två av områdena statistik, dataanalys, data engineering och data science.
Arbete med dataanalys och rapportskapande i PowerBI eller liknande BI-verktyg eller plattform.
Det är meriterande om du har:
arbetat med data engineering och/eller data science.
arbetat med molnbaserade lösningar för hantering av big data.
erfarenhet från någon av domänerna finans/ekonomi, produktion, marknad, energi, elhandel.
arbetat med agil arbetsmetodik.
Vill du veta mer?
Är du intresserad av tjänsten och vill ha mer information, vänligen kontakta rekryterande chef Rasmus Lind, 076-320 21 05. Facklig information lämnas av Carina Norberg, Unionen, 013-20 92 46, Henrik Kruuse af Verchou, Akademikerföreningen, 013-20 83 56 eller Martin Eriksson, SEKO, 013-20 83 06. Ansvarig för rekryteringsprocessen är HR-partner Linn Forslund, 013-20 94 13.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
Vi arbetar med en löpande urvalsprocess så skicka in din ansökan redan idag, men senast den 12 februari 2023.
Tekniska verken bedriver samhällsviktig verksamhet, och det kan därför bli aktuellt med en säkerhetsprövning i vissa rekryteringsprocesser. När det ska genomföras så informerar vi alltid kandidaterna om detta.
