Title: Future Talent Programme - Analyst Business Information & Analytics
Description:
At Tetra Pak we commit to making food safe and available, everywhere; and we protect what's good – protecting food, protecting people, and protecting the planet. By doing so we touch millions of people's lives every day. And we need people like you to make it happen.
Job Summary
Start your career development and become Tetra Pak’s next Future Talent! We are looking for highly motivated newly graduates to join us in 2023!

Future Talent Program is a Trainee Program within Tetra Pak. We offer a permanent position from start in September 2023 at our site in Lund. You will onboard an individual designed development program for 18 months connected to a specific position and the Tetra Pak organization. During the program you will participate in trainings and job rotations throughout various parts of Tetra Pak to explore your potential and grow as a person. As a Trainee here with us, you will get to know our entire business and collaborate with colleagues all over the world. And this is just the beginning of your Tetra Pak career!

Visit https://www.tetrapak.com/about/future-talent and read more about Tetra Pak Future Talent Program!

You will be based in Lund, Sweden but you will work in a global arena.
What you will do
As our new Future Talent – Analyst Business Information & Analytics you will:
Be part of Business Information & Analytics (BI&A) Center of Excellence (COE) coordinating BI&A activities in all geographies and business units
Contribute to defining Tetra Pak BI&A strategy and driving it implementation in the lines of business
Collaborate with various networks of Colleagues to deploy BI&A solutions
Learn best in class BI&A tools (Microsoft Power BI, KNIME, SAP HANA…) and transfer your knowledge to Tetra Pak Colleagues
Facilitate interactions between IT and Business
Roll-out of Data Science capabilities to business users
We believe you have
You have a Masters Degree in Computer Science/Engineering, Data Analytics and Business Economics, or Information Systems (Graduated 2022-2023)
It is possible that you have experience working in multi-cultural environment, proven to be independent self-learner.
You are fluent in English, written and spoken.
You have good communications skills, written and spoken
Previous international studies/experience are considered meritious
We Offer You
A variety of exciting challenges with ample opportunities for development and training in a truly global landscape
A culture that pioneers a spirit of innovation where our industry experts drive visible results
An equal opportunity employment experience that values diversity and inclusion
Market competitive compensation and benefits with flexible working arrangements

Apply Now
If you are inspired to be part of our promise to protect what’s good; for food, people, and the planet, apply with your CV and Cover Letter through our careers page at https://jobs.tetrapak.com/.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer som vill skapa framtida historia
Description:
Hej!

Hur vill du att framtiden ser ut?


Vi på Artificial Collective
vill skapa framtida historia med AI! Tillsammans med de mest passionerade inom AI/Data, inspirerar vi varandra varje dag och riktar vår samlade kunskap mot att skapa de bästa AI-lösningarna som bidrar med en större nytta. Både för samhället och enskilda företag.
Idag samarbetar vi med några av de mest spännande företagen i Norden!

Bli en del av teamet ‍‍
som idag består av seniora konsulter inom Data Science och Machine Learning. För att fortsätta arbeta med de mest spännande projekten, söker vi just nu efter vår nästa kollega inom Machine Learning.
Som anställd eller egen konsult hos Artificial Collective får du möjligheten att arbeta med just det ditt hjärta bultar extra för, oavsett om det gäller nyutveckling, vidareutveckling eller förvaltning. Både i individuella och i teamprojekt.
Du själv bestämmer över din tid, ersättning, vad du vill arbeta med och i vilken riktning du vill utvecklas. Som en del av Artificial Collective, får du en dedikerad agent som tillsammans med dig ser till att du kommer dit! Exempelvis genom utbildning, inspiration eller med hjälp av mentorskap från en expert inom önskat område.

Vi tror att du brinner för
Designa, bygga, driftsätta Machine Learning lösningar.

Ta komplex data till modeller och analyser som ger nya insikter.
Ta fram, träna och utvärdera ML-modeller för stora mängder användardata för att driva beslut.
Programmera i lämpligt språk så som Python, Scala och SQL.

Vårt löfte
är att ge dig vad du behöver för att du ska kunna lägga mer tid på det som ditt hjärta bultar extra för!
Vi tror på frihet och att det skapar välmående vilket vi ser som avgörande för passion samt geniala idéer.
Vi tror på passion och att det är viktigt för glädje och fortsatt lärande. Vi vill frigöra din passion.
‍‍ Vi tror på styrkan i att arbeta tillsammans och rikta vår kollektiva passion mot visionära idéer och skapa bättre lösningar.
Samtidigt får du det bästa paketet av förmåner.
Lön: 40-80k/månad
Semester: 30-60 betalda dagar
Pension: Ja
Försäkringar: Ja
Friskvård: Ja

Visst låter det intressant?
Sök direkt och var med och skapa den framtida historian du vill se när vi tillsammans tar nästa stora steg inom AI!

Title: (Senior) Data Engineer, Business Steering (Malmö) Group Digital, Ingka Group
Description:
Who you are

We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to join us in developing new revolutionizing ways for IKEA to build data products that support strategic decision making, performance management and data science. We are using cutting edge methodologies within cross-functional teams to keep IKEA leading in an exciting and fast-moving environment.
Our diverse and global team within Data & Analytics is growing even more and we would love to talk with you, if you recognize yourself in some of the following:

Strong knowledge of advanced data structures, distributed computing and cloud-based services
Strong knowledge of SQL for data processing and analysis
Extensive knowledge of programming languages (e.g. Java, Go, Python, or Scala), including concepts from functional and object-oriented programming paradigms
Broad knowledge of new and emerging tools for extracting, ingesting, and processing of large datasets (Apache Spark, Beam, Kafka, or equivalent)
Good knowledge of data science and business intelligence products and how they rely on data feeds for their implementation
Broad knowledge of digital product development principles and the importance of rapid validated learning cycles to optimise performance long term
Broad knowledge of collaborative software engineering practices (Git, Agile, DevOps), in which solutions evolve through the effort of self-organising cross-functional teams
A team player who takes ownership, builds cross-functional relationships with senior peers and loves sharing knowledge with more junior team members
A curious world class problem solver who wants to keep learning!
Experience with cloud platforms like Google Cloud Platform, AWS or Azure
Work Experience of 5 years in a similar role

This is our wish list! If you don’t recognize yourself in all these points, you might still be an excellent candidate for the role. We like to think long-term and invest in people’s development together with us.
The IKEA culture and values are very much a part of our business and day to day work life. For you to thrive and grow with IKEA it’s important for us that you share our values! You can read more regarding our values and life at IKEA on our website www.ikea.com.

What you'll be doing day to day

You’ll lead the transformation of IKEA into a more data driven company by ensuring that data and insights are frequently and widely used in product teams in Group Digital to reinforce, alter, or largely impact present and future decisions on business and product strategy.

As a Senior Data Engineer you will work closely with Data Scientists and Data Analysts to drive the development of data products within the Business Support domain. Here, we are building the systems and tools for steering and planning our business at scale, often for top management stakeholders. You will work hands-on with building data pipelines in our data mesh on Google Cloud Platform, as well as be a thought partner on questions like:

What data products do we design, build, test and maintain to promote data consumption?
How should we extract, merge, transform and serve data to enable usage at global scale?
What user needs do we prioritise first, making the optimal trade-off between quick business impact and building for the future?
What data products and mindsets should we evolve to empower not only our Data Analysts and Scientists, but all co-workers?
How can we ensure the reliability, security, and quality of the data, and how do we educate team members in cross-functional teams about the importance of it?
How can we transform a business problem into requirements for building data infrastructure?
How do we set up different environments (e.g. dev, test, prod) with appropriate security levels and data privacy requirements?
How should we coach and develop our junior team members to become world class Data Engineers?

And perhaps you have your own ideas on problems to solve? We are on a journey towards becoming a data-driven company and you will have the opportunity to help shape our path, based on your knowledge and experience.

Our team within Ikea

You will work in Data & Analytics together with other Data Engineers, Data Scientists, Data Analysts, Machine Learning Engineers, Data Stewards and Data Architects. Together you will be joining cross-functional teams consisting of colleagues from Technology, Product and Design from the business domain of Business Support. All of you together will be creating the best solutions to support strategic enterprise decisions, financial forecasting and business planning.

IKEA has long been a global leader in home furnishing. We are proud of our vision to improve the everyday life of the many people. But our industry is quickly changing, and we need to adapt to stay competitive. To facilitate our digital growth ambition, we are working in different locations world-wide. The home office for this role will be Malmö, Sweden, but we act as one global team and work together on global solutions.

We see so many opportunities for what we can accomplish and have the ambition to be a world class team. At the same time, we believe that our work is not just about solving business problems, but also about learning and having fun together.

WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU

Work on some exciting problems as described above, and you are encouraged to spot new opportunities or to collaborate with Data & Analytics colleagues in other specialist teams
Opportunities to have global impact with your work
Flexible and modern tools: we deploy on Google Cloud Platform and we use a lot of open-source tools across the board
Hardware and Operating System your choice
A team of great colleagues to learn with and from (with world-class experience across all aspects of Data & Analytics)
Continuous learning (we aim to spend 20% of our working time on learning)
Flexible and friendly working environment in a truly value-based company
Relocation support where applicable

Questions and support? Let's connect!

Does this sound like your next challenge? IKEA offers an exciting and empowering work environment in a global workplace. And as the world’s leader at life at home, you have exceptional opportunities to grow and develop together with us.

If you have questions regarding the role, recruitment process or other practicalities please reach out to Carl-Johan Andersson at carl-johan.andersson@ingka.ikea.com.
Please apply with your application in English. Note that we cannot process any applications through email. Thank you!

Title: Lead Data Scientist
Description:
ArabyAds was founded in 2013 and we help our clients to acquire customers at scale using data & technology across diverse set of digital advertising inventories which are managed through four of our platforms i.e. Checkout (social commerce), iConnect (influencer marketing), Adfalcon (programmatic advertising) & DeviceBoost. ArabyAds is proud to be an equal opportunity employer regardless of your race, colour, gender, religion, age, disability, or marital status. Define, build, and lead a team of Data Scientists.
Design, develop and deploy Data Science projects that are production-ready, robust and optimized.
Implement data flow solutions that process data real time on message streams from source systems.
Evaluate and enhance deployed Machine Learning models.
Discover areas of the company’s processes that can be leverage machine learning
Demonstrate thorough technical knowledge of Statistical modeling, Probability and Decision theory, Operations Research techniques and other quantitative modeling techniques
Work closely with internal stakeholders like the business teams, engineering teams and partner teams and align them with respect to your focus area
Implementing and operating stable, scalable data flow solutions from production systems into end-user facing applications/reports. These solutions will be fault tolerant, self-healing and adaptive.
Work with business owners to develop and define key business questions and to build data sets that answer those questions.
Requirements:
5+ year hands-on experience with Data Science project and implementing Machine learning Models.
2+ years of experience managing Data Science teams and DS projects
An MS or PhD degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Machine Learning or related technical field
Experience in Machine learning algorithms (decision trees, multivariate and logistic regression, kNN, kMeans, etc.)
Experience in projects involving cross-functional teams
Knowledge of various machine learning techniques and key parameters that affect their performance
Depth and breadth in quantitative knowledge. Excellent quantitative modeling, statistical analysis skills and problem-solving skills
Experience processing, filtering, and presenting large quantities (Millions to Billions of rows) of data
Combination of deep technical skills and business savvy enough to interface with all levels and disciplines within our customer’s organization
Demonstrable track record of dealing well with ambiguity, prioritizing needs, and delivering results in a dynamic environment
Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to effectively advocate technical solutions to research scientists, engineering teams and business audiences
Ability to develop experimental and analytic plans for data modeling processes, use of strong baselines, ability to accurately determine cause and effect relations
Demonstrable track record of dealing well with ambiguity, prioritizing needs, and delivering results in a dynamic environment

Title: Data Analyst for R&D Validation
Description:
Northvolt is now looking for a Data Analyst to be part of our growing validation team in Västerås. This is your chance to contribute to the development of the world's greenest and most sustainable Li-ion battery cell!
The Validation team is working directly with the customer projects and cell development to ensure the excellent performance & safety of Northvolts products – the batteries. Increasing amount of test demands especially in performance and life testing generate huge amounts of data, which need to be processed, visualized, and summarized.
As a Data Analyst for validation, you will be providing data analysis tools (in python) for validation, support with data visualization and generated automated data summaries. You will be collaborating closely with Northvolt’s data team to ensure efficient usage of the generated data.
Key responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Create visualizations and reports validating the performance of our lithium-ion cells
Develop data analysis standards and tools for automated analysis
Share knowledge in collaborative data analysis using modern data science tooling, growing the entire team
Collaborate with Data Engineers to design and implement a data lifecycle for the Validation Engineering application
Ideally, you have gathered first knowledge about battery testing or battery data analysis related to automotive industry or similar. You like to work and communicate with colleagues from various backgrounds. You have an eye for detail, while at the same time keeping the larger picture in sight. You are organized, pragmatic and keep an overview when working on different tasks. You are a curious, passionate life-long learner, who takes ownership and is eager to collaborate to improve the ways of data handling.

Title: Estonian Speaking Customer Service Agent
Description:
Customer Service Agent - Estonia
THE OPPORTUNITY
Do you have an interest in fashion, see solutions rather than problems and always strive to provide service at a top level? Then this opportunity might be the one for you.
Do you also value a dynamic and international work environment, fun and knowledgeable colleagues as well as a lot of internal career opportunities, then apply and get the chance to join our amazing Customer Service Team.
As our new Customer Service Agent you will join a team, where you together will work towards providing world class service to our customers.

WHAT YOU WILL DO
The first part of your journey at Boozt will be to take part in a thorough training program to create the best possible conditions for you to succeed and excel in your new role. Training sessions and development meetings will be held continuously throughout your time at Boozt.
Together with our trainers you will focus on your development and take part in training sessions to tailor your journey as a Boozter.
Provide top class service to our customers with all inquiries coming in via phone, email or chat
Be our expert when it comes to questions ranging from specific product information, to styling tips, stock status, shipping details, payment queries, and campaign errands
You will be the company’s eyes and ears and will be a truly important part of the “from order to delivery chain” to ensure that we reach our goal of building an unrivaled customer experience

YOUR PROFILE
You speak and write fluently in Estonian.
You are also fluent in English since this is our corporate language and it is a part of your daily tasks to support other markets when needed
You enjoy solving problems, exceeding expectations and has a natural ability to connect with people
You see no obstacles in the challenges of offering quick, informative and individual answers and explanations even in stressful times
Previous experience in the service industry is a plus
Good communication skills and a real interest in expressing yourself well, both in speech and writing (tests will be given as part of our recruitment process)
You are proud of being precise and it is natural for you to be considerate in your behavior both internally and externally

OUR OFFER
This is a chance for you to join our vibrant Customer Service Team, an opportunity to grow and develop with one of the leading Nordic E-commerce companies
Full-time temporary employment for an initial 12 months with the possibility for a permanent position (the employment will start with a 6 month probation period)
Working hours for the Estonian teams are 8:00-17:00 and 10:00-19:00 on a rolling schedule.
Your working schedule will be published for you to see four months in advance
You will join a big international team where we support and learn from each other, but the most important of all we have fun while doing so

Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.

We look forward to your application!

BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?

We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.

Title: Strategy Consultants
Description:
Deloitte is a leading global provider of audit and assurance, consulting, financial advisory, risk advisory, tax, and related services. During its 175-year history, our organization has grown tremendously in both scale and capabilities. Deloitte currently has approximately 415,000 people in more than 150 countries and territories, and serves four out of five Fortune Global 500® companies. Yet, our shared culture and mission—to make an impact that matters—remains unchanged. This is evident not only in Deloitte’s work for clients, but also in our WorldClass ambition, our WorldClimate initiative and our ALL IN diversity and inclusion strategy.
Are you ready for the next step in your career and to be part of our successful team in Sweden?
Deloitte's business area Consulting is a market leader in Sweden and works together with decision-makers in both global and local organizations.

Job description
Our Strategy team supports organizations in future proofing their businesses by enabling, creating and accelerating growth strategies. We invent, launch and scale game-changing businesses with the most influential corporates in the Nordics. Our market offerings in focus are:
Innovation & Ventures: Creating new business models for innovative and disruptive growth and accelerating through investments and acquisitions of startups
Sustainability Strategy & Transformation: Developing and integrating sustainability strategy with corporate strategy and realizing commercial opportunities related to sustainable change, e.g. through circular business models
Business Design & Configuration: Enabling growth by re-designing existing business models and defining future capabilities and operating model
Organic Growth: Designing customer strategies and go-to-market approaches for attracting new and retaining current customers
We are continuing our ambitious growth journey by looking to recruit the following roles:
Experienced leaders and strategy consultants within Insurance, Banking, Retail & Consumer Products, Sustainability and Analytics
Strategy management consultants on all levels

Insurance
As an experienced leader and strategy consultant within Insurance, you will have a critical role in scaling our already established partnerships with key clients as well as establishing solid partnerships with new target clients. You will join a team and network with a strong local and global track record and qualifications within the Property & Casual and Life & Pension industry segments.

As part of our Nordic Monitor Insurance strategy team, you will have the opportunity to work with our most senior insurance strategy leaders as well as clients across the Nordics. Typical projects include strategies related to products, distribution channels, partnerships, innovation, claims and underwriting as well as product design and similar topics.

Banking
As an experienced leader and strategy consultant within Banking, you will have a critical role in scaling our already established partnerships with key clients as well as establishing solid partnerships with new target clients. You will join a team and network with a strong local and global track record and qualifications within the Banking industry.

Sustainability
As an experienced leader and strategy consultant within Sustainability, you will have a critical role in developing and scaling our market offering Sustainability Strategy and Transformation as well as embedding sustainability perspectives in all our strategy engagements and across Deloitte. You will be part of creating and delivering our positioning and go-to-market strategy locally with the support from our broader Strategy team and our global network.

Retail & Consumer Products
As an experienced leader and strategy consultant within Retail & Consumer Products, you will have a critical role in scaling our already established partnerships with key clients as well as establishing solid partnerships with new target clients. You will join a team and network with a strong local and global track record and qualifications within Retail and the broader Consumer Products industry.

Analytics
As an experienced leader and strategy consultant within Analytics, you will have a critical role in embedding the power of data and analytics in all our strategy engagements and across Deloitte. You will be part of creating and delivering our go-to-market strategy locally with the support from our broader Strategy team and our global network.

Qualifications
We are looking for people with the ability and proven experience to think strategically and creatively by combining business strategy and analysis with expressing new ideas and opportunities. You are a powerful storyteller with an intuitive ability to present complex concepts in a clear, concise and compelling way.

You need to be passionate about leading and inspiring our cross-functional teams (business, tech, analytics, creative and design) and developing our internal team capabilities. You should have a relentless curiosity, be comfortable in a fast-paced environment, and be able to leverage established relations as well as source our global network and ecosystem.

We are looking for
Senior Consultant, Manager and Senior Manager levels
Work experience from a leading strategy or management consulting firm
Proven project leader, you are experienced in leading project teams in growth, innovation and digital strategy or sustainability, working collaboratively with a diverse team of stakeholders
An understanding and an established focus within one of our main industries (Insurance, Banking, Retail & Consumer Products), Sustainability and/or Analytics & Data Science
Excellent problem solving and analytical skills
Excellent written and verbal ability in Swedish and English
An established focus within one of our market offerings is preferable
Readiness to travel (to some extent)
Location Stockholm or Malmö

We offer
At Deloitte we focus on helping people at every level of their career to identify and use their strengths. By on-the-job learning experiences, formal development programs at Deloitte University and support from a personal coach, you will have a variety of opportunities to continue to grow throughout your career. The way of working at Deloitte – our commitment to you. At Deloitte we foster a collaborative culture where talented individuals can produce their best work. We value innovative thinking, diverse insights and a genuinely distinctive level of customer service. We value difference with respect at the heart of our inclusive culture. Our role is to unlock potential for growth and innovation. We believe this requires real collaboration – with our own networks and with our clients. It’s why we commit to truly getting under the skin of our client’s needs, developing a full appreciation for their environment, goals and ambitions. We often work hand-in-hand with our clients to help find the right solution and to help to apply that solution. Our aim is to leave behind ambassadors who are equipped to continue the transformation we have started.

How to apply
Your application should consist of a CV and a cover letter and you apply directly online.

As a qualitative part of Deloitte's recruitment process, our final candidates undergo a background check, to increase awareness of our future employees, secure the working environment for our employees and meet regulatory requirements. The background check process is carried out in collaboration with ToFindOut. https://tofindout.se/en/background-check/

Questions?
If you have any questions regarding the role, please contact Ajla Talovic, atalovic@deloitte.se. For questions regarding the application process, please contact Sophie Karlerö, skarlero@deloitte.se.

We are looking forward to your application!

For further information on Deloitte, please visit www.deloitte.se

What impact will you make?
Every day, your work will make an impact that matters, while you thrive in a dynamic culture of inclusion, collaboration and high performance. We do not just aspire to make solutions. We wish to create an impact that makes a positive and crucial difference for the people around us, our clients and our society. Deloitte is where you’ll find unlimited opportunities to succeed and realize your full potential.

Title: Data Science Consultant

At TT PSC, we do understand the importance of data and analytics, hence investing heavily in this domain. Title: Product Designer
Description:
THE OPPORTUNITY
Are you a creative soul, bubbly of ideas and not afraid to break new grounds? Then this is the position for you. As a designer you will be involved throughout the entire product development lifecycle, from brainstorming the initial concepts together with business and stakeholders to doing research, creating the final UI designs and delivering assets to the developers.
You will be part of the Platform Team that works on all the tech that runs Boozt. Here you will get the chance to lead design projects for various stakeholders in the company on both our commercial products but also on our internal systems.
You will join a small team with experienced colleagues that ships fast, but always with an intention to learn.
The position is located in our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden. We expect you to be able to travel to Boozt Innovation Lab in Copenhagen, Denmark when required or approximately once a week / biweekly.
WHAT YOU WILL DO
You will be working in the product design team within the organization and collaborate with fellow designers and developers from different departments on a daily basis.
Work closely and collaboratively with project managers and software engineers by sharing insights and explaining design rationales.
You’ll be working on both the customer facing products but also on our internal tools built by development teams inhouse.
Translate insights and business requirements into product design concepts and create intuitive end-to-end experiences that bring delight to our customers.
Bring concepts to life by iteratively creating prototypes to reduce complexity and simplify the user journey.
Be the voice of our customers by leading your projects with insights-driven design methods and identifying opportunities to make our products more joyful and usable.
Articulate to the stakeholders how your design decisions solve the business requirements and help improve the user experience.
*
YOUR PROFILE*
At least 2 years of working experience in product design.
A portfolio showcasing design problems, context, process and solutions. We will only consider applications with a portfolio.
Experience in creating designs and prototypes using Figma and Principle/Protopie or a similar tool.
You’ll stand out from the crowd if you have experience working with and creating design systems in large organizations.
Comfortable working across multiple projects at once.
Fluent in English. Note that we only consider English applications.
To be successful in this role you are result driven, not afraid of pushing your surroundings when needed in order to reach the goal. You enjoy working in a fast paced environment where you get the trust, freedom and responsibility to manage your own work.
Welcome to apply for the position!
BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development

Driven and passionate international colleagues

Title: Data Provisioning Lead
Description:
Data Provisioning Lead
Macclesfield UK, Warsaw PLN, Barcelona ESP, Gothenburg SWE
Competitive Salary + Benefits
Be empowered to be innovative and creative where difference is valued
Would you like to be a part of a Data Science & Artificial Intelligence (DS&AI) group who has direct strategic impact on drug development, playing a key role in getting medicines to patients?
At AstraZeneca, we are constantly pushing the boundaries of science to deliver life-changing medicines to patients, with a real passion for discovery and a pipeline to show for it. Here, you’ll have the opportunity to make a difference in people’s lives every single day.
Data Science & Artificial Intelligence (DS&AI) group who has direct strategic impact on drug development, playing a key role in getting medicines to patients?
At AstraZeneca, we are constantly pushing the boundaries of science to deliver life-changing medicines to patients, with a real passion for discovery and a pipeline to show for it. Here, you’ll have the chance to create a difference in people’s lives every single day.
AstraZeneca is investing in data management and analysis capabilities, through its long-term Growth Through Innovation Strategy. The DS&AI team collaborates across R&D to drive innovation through data science and AI. Together we seek to:
Improve our understanding of disease and uncovering new targets
Transform R&D processes
Speed the design and delivery of new medicines for patients
The R&D Data Office, within DS&AI, is a key organisation to deliver upon AstraZeneca’s strategy. Data Office operates a central capability, with R&D wide accountability, to ensure that we harness the power of data to drive innovative science. Data Office will govern data, drive data quality and ensure our data is readied for analytics, crafting paved-paths for scientists to perform data-driven research, without compromising our legal restrictions or ethical principles.
Within Data Office, your role is Data Provisioning Lead, a member of a dedicated Data Provisioning Operations team. In this role you will coordinate end-to-end activities associated to Data Provisioning including: Collaborating closely with partners; performing risk assessment associated to data-sharing, with emphasis on AstraZeneca’s four sharing principles; business sensitivity, legal rights, ethical and scientific merit; and coordinate cross-team activities to achieve delivery outcomes.
Crucially, your role will drive the maintenance and improvement of the four sharing principles to make data available for re-use within or outside AstraZeneca.
To be successful in this role you must have excellent critical thinking skills, enjoy succeeding in task-orientated goals, and be able to communicate with partners from different experience levels and cultures.
This is an opportunity to secure a unique, centralised role within AstraZeneca, joining a team of highly motivated people in a truly global organisation.
Tasks and responsibilities
Coordinate data provisioning requests and associated information.
Ensure that data requestor needs are met as each request goes through the process.
Assess requests and assign an appropriate service level for request fulfilment
Responsible for tracking progress of request, ensure relevant information is gathered as part of request and responsible for keeping each request running smoothly.
Acting as a central coordinator for projects requiring cross-functional activities, including arranging, hosting and minuting meetings, coordinating actions to-time and to-task.
Monitor request progress, handle and seek mitigation for any issues that might arise.
Work with the Data Provisioning team and other partners to eliminate blockers.
Ensure data sharing standards and requirements are met, bringing in other specialists where clarifications are required.
Use tools to monitor progress on requests.
Support the Data Provisioning team in considering ways to improve processes and value to our customers.
Contribute to department metrics on performance efficiency
Minimum requirements
Proven work experience as a Project Leader/Manager or similar role
Ability to handle partner requirements
Strong communication and teamwork skills
Must have a high level attention to details
Excellent communication skills, an ability to create relationships with many different levels and cultures and be detail focused.
Some experience in project management
Solid organizational skills, including multitasking and time-management
BSc in Business Administration, related field, or equivalent professional experience
Leadership Core Capabilities: Influencing, innovation, business awareness
Preferred experience and key factors
Experience from Pharma industry is a plus.
For the right candidate, there are opportunities to for career progression both within the Data Provisioning team, within the Data Office and more widely within AstraZeneca.
Why we love it
If your passion is science and you want to be part of a team that makes a bigger impact on patients’ lives, then there’s no better place to be. Here we truly understand science and apply it every day to strengthen and grow our pipeline.
So, what’s next?
Are you already imagining yourself joining our team? Good, because we can’t wait to hear from you.
Are you ready to bring new ideas and fresh thinking to the table? Brilliant! We have one seat available and we hope it’s yours.
Where can I find out more?

Follow AstraZeneca on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/astrazenecacareers/
Follow AstraZeneca on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/astrazeneca_careers/?hl=en

Title: Graduate Acceleratorprogram inom Business Intelligence
Description:
Augusti 2023 drar vårt Graduate Accelerator Program för Data & Analytics igång! Är du nyfiken på konsultrollen? Vill du jobba med spännande värdeskapande projekt tillsammans med ett sammansvetsat team? Hos Columbus ges du möjlighet att växa på ett internationellt bolag med nordisk prägel och globala kunder!
Vårt Accelerator Program ger dig möjligheten att skapa en framgångsrik konsultkarriär hos ett företag som vill satsa på din kompetensutveckling och din framtid. Du blir anställd som Associate Consultant inom Data & Analytics och under dina första sex månader kommer du delta i ett strukturerat program med fokus på din professionella och personliga utveckling. Som Associate Consultant i våra olika kundprojekt är du en viktig del av ett tätt sammansvetsat projektteam som består av kunniga och hjälpsamma kollegor, tillsammans arbetar ni med den senaste tekniken inom Business Intelligence och Data Science. Kika in här för att ta del av vad våra tidigare Acceleratorer har uppskattat med programmet!

Programmet har ett begränsat antal platser i Göteborg och Malmö och vi intervjuar löpande – så skicka in din ansökan idag!

Vad innehåller programmet?
Soft skills som konsultmannaskap, presentationsteknik, globalt samarbete och projektmetodik
Praktisk kunskap i de senaste verktygen inom dataanalys genom e-learning och lärarledd undervisning/Q&A
Kundprojekt där du kommer ut i verkligheten och deltar i implementationsprojekt
Under programmets gång introduceras du till flera business intelligence verktyg som exempelvis Microsoft Power BI, Infor Birst, Qlik och Tableau och du arbetar med olika verktyg för datahantering. Många av våra kunder befinner sig i molnet och programmet ger dig grundläggande kunskap om plattformar som Azure. Vid intresse finns även möjlighet att på längre sig fördjupa sig inom avancerad dataanalys, AI och machine learning.
Du tilldelas en personliga mentor som ger dig strukturerad vägledning och hjälper dig att växa in i din roll som framgångsrik konsult. Vi ser långsiktigt på dig som medarbetare. Därför kommer vi tillsammans att sätta upp en utvecklingsplan för dig som sträcker sig ca 2-3 år framåt i tiden
Efter utbildningen
Arbetar du som konsult med att vara delaktig i att leda kunden i sitt transformationsprojekt
Har du fått värdefull praktisk kunskap som du använder för att vägleda våra kunder att arbeta smartare i sina affärsprocesser.
Har du skaffat dig mycket goda karriärmöjligheter - likväl i Sverige som globalt!
Vem är du?
Du har ett intresse för verksamhets- och affärsprocesser och trivs i dialog med kund. Du har mycket god kommunikationsförmåga och vill etablera långsiktiga relationer med våra kunder. Du har en god analytisk förmåga och är nyfiken på hur teknik kan öka värdet för våra kunder. Vi förväntar oss att du är en lagspelare – för vi jobbar i team. ‍‍
Högskoleutbildning inom information-, system- eller datavetenskap eller motsvarande program
Grundläggande kunskaper i databaser, modellering och SQL
Mycket goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska i tal och skrift
Har du jobbat något eller några år efter examen är det ett extra plus.
Är du redo för en utmaning?
För att delta i programmet, behöver du investera i din utveckling och ditt lärande. Programmet är intensivt och inlärningskurvan brant. Detta kräver engagemang och målmedvetenhet från din sida. I gengäld ger vi dig en accelererad karriärmöjlighet i en högkompetent och kreativ kultur, där vi har kul på jobbet! Våra kunder litar på att vi guidar dem till den bästa lösningen så du är en viktig kugge i vår leverans av affärskritiska system. Du är med och påverkar våra kunders affär och hjälper dem att optimera sina processer. Skratt och skämt är vardag och vi ser fram emot att träffa varandra på måndag morgon.
Ansökan och nästa steg
Hos oss kan du ansöka med din LinkedIn och/eller CV och du behöver inte fylla i några långa frågeformulär. Vi vill ha en rättvis och objektiv rekryteringsprocess som möjligt. Därför ingår det ett logik- och personlighetstest under processens gång. Intervjuer kommer hållas löpande. Frågor? Hör av dig till ansvarig rekryterare Malin Nyberg.
Varför Columbus?
Vi har i över 30 år levererat digitala lösningar till våra kunder och det har vi gjort framgångsrikt. Hur kommer det sig? Jo! På Columbus har vi en omfattande branschkunskap som kombineras med ett stort utbud av digitala lösningar och en rejäl dos kundförståelse. Våra olika affärsområden kan dra nytta av varandra och arbeta med samma kunder i olika skeden av sin digitalisering och därmed erbjuda olika spetskompetenser. Vi hjälper våra kunder att forma lösningar efter branschspecifika behov så att de kan nå sin fulla digitala potential.
På Data & Analytics får du vara delaktig i ett område som är strategiskt viktigt för Columbus. Vi är en grupp på 50 konsulter i Skandinavien och vi växer! Columbus är ledande inom Dynamics 365, M3 samt E-Commerce vilket ger oss ett stort internationellt kontaktnät av konsulter. Våra kunder och vår spetskompetens ligger inom tillverkande industri, food & beverage och fashion. Vi tror på att utveckla oss själva och därigenom våra kunder genom att använda oss av den senaste tekniken, som du såklart kommer kunna hålla dig uppdaterad inom.

Jobba på Columbus
Columbus är ett värdestyrt bolag med engagerade medarbetare som stöttar varandra i både framgång som motgång. Att ha en god balans mellan arbete och fritid är en självklarhet. Det kan vara allt från hämtning och lämning på förskola till väntan av det där paketet som ska levereras hem ”någon gång mellan 10-19”. Vi lämnar utrymme för återhämtning och ser till att arbeta proaktivt med blicken på horisonten. Dessutom så är vi riktigt bra på att fira framgångar och det är inte ovanligt med fika, lyxfrukost och AW på kontoret.
Vi lever efter våra värdeord – Stay Curious, Build Trust, Collaborate och Deliver Customer Success. ️
Spana in vårt Insta-flöde för att få en bild av hur det är att jobba hos oss genom våra kollegor. Klicka på bilden för att komma till Instagram-kontot.
Helt ofiltrerat har vi samlat in omdömen från nuvarande och tidigare kollegor. Klicka nedan för att läsa mer.

Title: Global Data Governance Lead
Description:
If you have knowledge in data management with experience in the implementation of Data Governance, and would like to apply your experience in a company that follows the science, the Senior Global Data Governance Lead role is for you!
AstraZeneca is at an exciting time of new products and launches. We get to work with innovative and scientific products on our leading-edge end to end supply chain, using the latest technologies and modern facilities.
In Operations, we have a big ambition – to deliver more medicines to patients, quicker and more affordably. Backed by the investment, leadership, and a clear plan to get there, we bring personal dedication and out-of-the-box thinking.
Join the team where everyone feels a personal connection to the people that we impact. From our science labs to manufacturing at scale, we are committed to delivering at the highest quality. It’s inspiring and exciting work, influencing every part of the product lifecycle to deliver life-changing medicines. To ultimately make people’s lives better – from patients and their families to all of us in society.
In this role, you will provide global leadership for range of Data Governance strategies to manage and protect Operations data assets, so that they can be used with confidence to maximize value for the enterprise, while legal, ethical and security aspects are safeguarded. The role will provide strategic leadership in one or several of the following specialist areas: data governance strategy & operations, data standards management, data quality management, data policy, compliance & risk management.
Leadership to manage a diverse range of activities through others including deep technical data governance and advising on/leading cutting-edge projects on a global basis. Responsible for the development of Global Data Governance strategy, goals and roadmap, within a specified area, aligned to the AZ wide strategy.
What you will do:

Title: Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD
Description:
Join us on our journey to net zero and make an impact on the mobility of tomorrow. We are looking for a Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD to join our R&D team.
Aurobay has over hundred years of heritage in creating premium quality engines. With homes in Sweden and China, we have a strong reputation for pioneering practices in the automotive industry. We pride ourselves in our attention to detail and commitment to excellence.

Your role at Aurobay
Our team currently consists of six data scientists, SW engineers, and model-based calibration engineers. We develop new methods for measurement data collection and analysis to help R&D become more efficient and data driven. We also work closely with other advanced engineering teams.
As Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD, you will:
Train and evaluate ML models for predicting emissions
Work closely together with subject matter experts to align data/measurement requirements and incorporate physical models into the model
Optimize algorithm memory and CPU load for predictions on the edge together with function developers
You will also use the data we are collecting in our rigs to build models for predicting engine emissions of hazardous species. The models can be used both offline in the development phase, and on the edge for On-Board Monitoring (OBM) and On-Board Diagnostics (OBD) in our customer vehicles. As part of this job, you’ll have the opportunity develop your own machine-learning projects together with the rest of the team. We give our engineers the freedom and time for their own projects, to try out new ideas and fine-tune their skills.
What we offer
In addition to a competitive salary, a great location on Lindholmen, and a genuine work-life balance, we provide the following benefits:
A yearly wellness contribution of SEK 5 000 for your physical and mental wellbeing.
A personal and professional development scheme to support your growth.
Want to drive a car? – Discount to buy a car, and a competitive leasing cost for a company car.
Additional pension funding.
Competitive additional and full coverage insurance.


Do you fit the profile?
You hold a master’s degree or higher in data science, mathematics, statistics, physics or relevant fields.
You have strong programming skills in Python, Julia, or MATLAB.
You also have experience in ML algorithms such as linear regression, artificial neural networks, and boosted decision tree regression.
Good to have familiarity with:
Time series modeling, especially ML algorithms that can be used for time series such as recurrent neural networks, convolutional neural networks, or transformers
Internal Combustion Engines
Chemical models for catalytic converters
Embedded systems
At Aurobay, we are committed to diversity and inclusion. We welcome applicants from all backgrounds and believe that different perspectives and experiences make for a stronger, more innovative company.
How to apply
To apply, please submit your application via the link below. Deadline to submit your application is 31st of January, but the selection process will be running continuously. Please note that due to GDPR, we do not accept applications via email.
We can’t wait to see what you can bring to our team!
Questions
If you have any additional questions regarding the position, you are welcome to contact recruiting manager Erik Fyrk, erik.fyrk@aurobay.com. For questions regarding the recruitment process please contact Recruiter Felicia Eriksson, felicia.eriksson@aurobay.com.

Title: Engineering Manager - Data Science Platform
Description:
We are looking for an experienced Engineering Manager to join Northvolt's Data Platform within the Digitalization department. You will join and lead the team that designs, builds, and operates the Data Platform supporting Battery Cell Factory Operations.
Our factories produce large amounts of heterogenous data that get uploaded to our cloud platform, and are then processed, organized, and ready for analysis. You will partner cross-functionally with the Engineering, Production and Quality teams in the factories to drive data-driven manufacturing operations. We strive to use technology and data to co-develop solutions that matter, and welcome applicants from diverse experience levels and backgrounds.
We are searching for someone passionate about building diverse, inclusive and highly effective teams. The ideal candidate is a curious life-long learner who takes ownership and is eager to collaborate to build better products. This role is a vital member of the Ett Digitalization team is key to Northvolt's mission to enable the future of energy.
Our Connected Factory architecture is described in the AWS/Northvolt blog post https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/industries/northvolts-next-gen-connected-factory-a-digital-blueprint-factory-built-from-scratch/
We presented our vision and progress at AWS re:Invent 2022 (Northvolt part starts at 32:14) AWS re:Invent 2022 - How innovators are driving more sustainable manufacturing (SUS312)
Key responsibilities include
Lead a full-sized Data Team (7-10 people) of Data Engineers, Data Analytics Engineers, and Data Scientists through hiring, coaching, mentoring, feedback and hands-on career development
Drive and be accountable for technical delivery and work with your team on strategy, roadmap and execution
You'll work with others to shape how Northvolt’s data ecosystem works — you'll help develop our technical practices, recruiting and onboarding strategy, planning and prioritization process, and more.
Advocate operational excellence and advance high-quality development practices
Grow a healthy, collaborative engineering culture in line with the company values
Be an active part of the leadership team and collaborate with other leaders in the organization
Grow the technical expertise of the team
Apply with CV and cover letter or your complete LinkedIn profile.
Full-time employment, fixed salary.
Location: Stockholm, Sweden.
Travel: Skellefteå 2-3 days/week, 2 weeks/month during the first 6 months.
Skills & Requirements
Preferred Experience
Communication, communication, communication. You communicate fluently and humbly with all types of different humans choosing effective methods based on context, audience and purpose
Proven track record of hiring, developing and growing people. You’re committed to building diverse and inclusive teams; you value empathetic and direct communication and foster environments that are at once collaborative, empowering, supportive, and challenging—ones where people do their best work
Engineering in technical data role (Data Engineering, Data Science, Machine Learning) including processing, storage, quality, and management on GCP or AWS
Working with a diverse set of stakeholders and helping them understand the trade-offs to different product and technical decisions
Not Required (bonus points)
[Bonus] You've experienced the challenges of scaling and re-architecting data platforms and infrastructure through orders of magnitude of growth
[Bonus] Experience hands-on designing and building highly scalable and reliable data architecture using Kinesis, Lambda, dbt, Parquet, Protobuf, Airflow, Redshift or equivalent stack
[Bonus] Engineering foundation understanding (electro/mechanical/chemical/physical), preferably within the energy domain
[Bonus] Experience from fast-growing start-ups or scale-ups
[Bonus] Experience from large (manufacturing) enterprises with heterogeneous and distributed data across many domains
Skills
Excellent English written and oral communication skills
Independent, organized and entrepreneurial
Passionate team collaborator that can thrive in a diverse international environment (110+ nationalities and counting)
Qualities that we value are flexibility, sense of quality, friendliness, motivation to take on new challenges, grit and a sense of humor
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment
Fast paced & entrepreneurial culture
Warrant program
Wellness grant

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
At Trustly, we’re passionate about simplifying the way people pay and get paid online. We’re a licensed payment institution and our B2B products available across Europe, North America and Australia attract global merchants in segments such as e-commerce, telecom, travel, financial services and gaming. In June 2018, private equity firm Nordic Capital acquired a majority stake in Trustly with ambitions to support us in becoming the leading global online banking payments provider.

We are a diverse and fast-growing team with our headquarters in Stockholm, Sweden, and 9 additional offices across Europe and North America. Together we are leading the development of the payments industry and the work you’ll do here will make a great impact.

About the role

Trustly is developing fast and so are the requirements on data being made available for analytics, data science, reporting and BI. The Data Engineering team’s part in this is to provide a platform and tools to enable data producers and consumers to share data in a frictionless way. Trustly’s European data platform is built on GCP using components such as Airflow (Cloud Composer), Beam (Dataflow), BigQuery, Pub/Sub and Google Cloud Storage. We also maintain the company’s dbt Cloud installation to enable Analytics Engineers and other downstream SQL power users to build their own data pipelines and not become dependent on a single data team that does everything. Parts of Trustly’s payment product run on AWS so knowledge about that ecosystem is important to us as well.
What you'll do:
Build and operate Trustly’s data lake on Google Cloud Storage/BigQuery
Develop and maintain batch and streaming data pipelines
Work with transformations of data from one or multiple source systems to feed our analytics and ML applications
Help data consumers within the company find the data they need and assist them with setting up pipelines and exports
Help us identify new use-cases for our data and work with stakeholders from the rest of the organization on how to realize those
Who you are:
MSc Software Engineering or equivalent
At least 1-3 years experience from a Developer role within the field of Data (Data- or Backend/Database Engineer)
Experience from building streaming data pipelines
Experience from building cloud data solutions (Prio1: GCP, Prio2: AWS)
Good coding skills with Python
Proficient in SQL

Title: Business Analyst
Description:
We are looking for a Business Analyst on-site in Malmo, The ideal candidate
has several years of experience in analytics and coding.
Roles & Responsibilities:
Bachelor's degree with an emphasis on coursework of a quantitative nature (Information Systems, Computer Science, Data Science or related area)
Experience in scripting with SQL and extracting large sets of data
Business analysis and requirements gathering abilities
Strong verbal and written communication skills
Strong collaboration skills to work with others towards the same outcome and drive results
Ability to learn new technology/business functions quickly through instruction and self- training
Knowledge of analytics languages like Python or R is a must
Have prior experience working with reporting BI tools and Snowflake data warehouse specifically. Knowledge of data pipeline automation is a plus.
Ability to lead a team and deliver is a plus.
Required Skills :
Demonstrated experience with data analysis, profiling, data cleansing and standardization Process
Analyze stakeholder reported data issues, performing root cause analysis, and identifying and implementing appropriate remediation
Excellent advanced SQL and analytical skills to query databases to perform data analysis to further enhance business analysis
Experience of Master data management business processes and MDM (Reltio like) platform skills around data stewardship
General knowledge of data quality framework processes.
Dashboard platforms like Tableau, scripting languages like Python, SQL etc. ability to build DQ dashboards
Excellent communication skills to communicate with various stakeholders including Technology Platform providers, data vendors and business communities

Title: Head of Analytics
Description:
Do you want to help us unleash the secret to how happy employees create a happy business? We are an innovative, agile, and continuously growing modern tech company on a path to improving the work lives of millions around the world.

We develop workforce management solutions - software that makes scheduling and time reporting more smooth and more flexible for almost a million users worldwide!
We value passion, creativity, quality, and simplicity. You’ll be given the opportunity to make an impact and directly contribute to our success, bring new ideas, and have full ownership of your area.
Our global team, of more than 35 nationalities, have fun together, whether it is during a typical Swedish Fika, a workshop, going for a run with a colleague, or spending time together during the annual company Goal trip, team kickoffs, or after-work socials. We have built a collaborative and friendly atmosphere here at Quinyx and are committed to sharing knowledge and supporting one another!
Are you curious and ready to take the first steps on an awesome journey and make magic happen with us? As a member of Quinyx, you will be part of an inclusive and diverse workplace where everyone is allowed to be themselves and thrive.

About the role
As a part of our growing analytics team, you will take part in developing tomorrow's intelligent workforce management, enabling insights driven decision-making and having a significant impact on strategic initiatives. The mission is to turn our vast amounts of data into actionable insights across the organisation and guide the development of new features and models. The Head of Analytics will lead our analytics team, and work closely with stakeholders and cross-functional teams to leverage data-driven insights to drive business growth. With our international presence, you will be an integral part of a company set out to enable our customers to create a happy business and a happy workforce.
Are you a data and analytics leader with a passion for driving analytics initiatives? Do you have a strong background in data engineering, data analysis, and data science, as well as technical proficiency in programming languages and tools? If so, we want you to lead our analytics team as our Head of Analytics.
What you’ll be doing
Lead a team within data analysis, data engineering, and data science to deliver high-quality insights, analysis, and models that inform key business decisions
Develop and drive the vision, strategy, and execution of the analytics function within the organisation
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities for data-driven innovation and optimization
Ensure the right technical capabilities, tools, and systems are in place to support the analytics efforts
Build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders to ensure alignment on analytics priorities and objectives
Mentor and develop team members to ensure they have the skills and knowledge needed to grow and deliver high-quality work
Stay ahead of industry trends and best practices
What you’ll bring to the team
MSc degree in Engineering, Physics, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, or equivalent quantitative field.
4+ years of experience managing data & analytics teams
Strong leadership skills and a track record of leading by example
Strong skill set and profound background in the data & analytics field spanning from data engineering, analysis to science.
Technical proficiency in programming languages and tools such as Python, Spark, SQL, R, and data visualisation tools.
Strategic mindset with great business acumen
Ability to build and maintain strong relationships with stakeholders at all levels of the organisation
Strong communication skills
Experience working within the SaaS space
What’s in it for you?
We promote and encourage a healthy lifestyle with flexible work hours and the latest tools, enhanced vacation allowance, wellness, home office, professional development contributions, virtual yoga classes, and last but not least, you will have the chance to participate in our well-known yearly ping-pong tournament!

Want to join Quinyx?
At Quinyx, we provide equal employment opportunities and strive for an inclusive, diverse, value-driven culture. All applications will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, disability, or veteran status.
Happy Workforce, Happy Business!

Title: Payroll & HR Specialist
Description:
THE OPPORTUNITY
Join our Payroll team as a Payroll & HR Specialist, and take lead in ensuring that we have the best process for a smooth monthly operation of our Payroll for our +500 employees in Sweden and Denmark. As a Payroll & HR Specialist we expect you to own the payroll process from A-Z as well as help and guide our Payroll Coordinators.
You will join an international team of HR and Payroll professionals, where we work together to make sure that we provide the best service possible to our employees.
WHAT YOU WILL DO
As our Payroll & HR Specialist you will participate in handling weekly expense reports.
Update, create and maintain employee files including personal data, salary, benefits, pension and insurance values. Answer staff inquiries regarding pay, holiday, parental leave, etc.
Lead the handling of the monthly Swedish and Danish payroll preparation and administration for our headquarters and store
Guide our Payroll Coordinators in advanced questions
Reconcile payroll, social charges, and taxes
Prepare reports and input to quarterly and annual statements
Handle annual calculation and reconciliation of vacation balances
Prepare and report monthly statistics to authorities
Act as a liaison with the social insurance authority (Försäkringskassan), our pension & insurance company, and the Swedish Migration Agency (Migrationsverket)
Create employment Contracts
*
YOUR PROFILE*
To be successful in this role you are detail-oriented, analytical, and proactive. You are reliable, flexible, and have good communication skills. You enjoy teamwork and have an organized way of working. To work in a fast-paced environment with multiple tasks motivates you.
*
Experience working with Visma Agda PS & Visma.net Expense
Proficient in Microsoft Word and Excel
Highly skilled and minimum 5 years of Swedish payroll administration experience
Strong understanding of Swedish payroll tax rules and labour laws
Basic understandings of Danish payroll tax rules and labor laws
Fluent in Swedish and English
Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.
We look forward to your application!
BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor
A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Business Development Manager - Nordics
Description:
Business Development Manager Nordics & Baltics
Nordic Countries (Sweden, Finland, Norway, Denmark & Iceland)
Baltic Countries (Estonia, Latvia & Lithuania)
Our client is a medical device company, focused on delivering clinically superior breakthrough solutions that will help patients get back to the things that matter. We are currently looking to recruit a Business Development Manager to cover the Nordics and Baltics. Our chosen candidate with be required to work in collaboration with marketing to develop the strategic and tactical plans and programs to achieve the business objectives for the respective markets. Coordinating and leading quarterly business reviews with sales teams and Key Distributors;

Consistently achieving sales results within the assigned region and with major healthcare accounts through the development of strategies and objectives, and through directing the development and implementation of tactical plans. He/she will deploy appropriate resources to achieve objectives.
On an ongoing basis collaborating with functional heads to innovate around value added initiatives to boost business performance, directly or indirectly, with key partners;
Driving a high performance culture by setting demanding and challenging personal and business objectives.

Minimum of 8-10 years proven success in sales, marketing and market development.
Prior/current business development/ Direct sales/distributor management experience required;
Strong analytical skills, including financial performance evaluation, portfolio assessment and development in building sustainable regional growth.

Experience of effectively working in a matrix organization and markets would be desirable
Experience in people management and leadership
Fluency in English, Swedish and another European language desirable.
High degree of initiative, professionalism, empathy and the ability to perform independently, comfortable working alone & unsupervised for periods of time
Outstanding communication skills and team-player
Evidenced problem solving skills and decision making ability
Ability to recognize and address process gaps
Willingness to travel internationally across EMEA
Cross-cultural awareness

Sales, Marketing or General management experience
Significant upward movement potential

Title: Principal Data & Analytics Architect
Description:
What makes us Qlik
Qlik helps enterprises around the world move faster, work smarter, and lead the way forward with an end-to-end solution for getting value out of data. A Gartner Magic Quadrant Leader for 12 years in a row! Our platform is the only one on the market that allows for open-ended, curiosity-driven exploration, giving everyone – at any skill level – the ability to make real discoveries that lead to real outcomes and transformative changes. We are a Values-Driven organization operating in over 100 countries with 38,000 customers around the world. If you think we are interesting, please read on – we may be looking for you!

Principal Data & Analytics Architect
The Principal Data & Analytics Architect’s main responsibility will be to, in conjunction with architecture leadership, identify, analyze and support the enterprise’s business drivers through enablement of data and/or information strategies.

The Senior architect will lead and support the development and evolution of Qlik’s data policies and approaches with a goal of enabling data analytics and data science. A data governance program and its standards will be pragmatically supported to derive optimum business value while ensuring data security and privacy requirements are fully met.

The successful candidate will possess excellent oral and written communication skills and extensive technology acumen which they use to drives results, and lead through influence. They must be able to build strong relationships by working collaboratively with all levels of the organization.

Responsibilities include:

Working across the organization to maintain a data strategy that adheres to the target architecture and roadmap which maximizes the value of information assets via their creation, access, and use.
Working with delivery and product teams to ensure that system designs comply with the target state architecture and help in the selection of product and / or solutions to deliver business outcomes.
Enabling desired business outcomes through analytics, governance, and enterprise information policy administration.
Ensuring that the enterprise architecture is used as a lens and filter to identify, prioritize and execute the data and analytic initiatives with clear line of sight to enterprise strategies and business outcomes.
Supporting the data and information governance model across all business units.
Maintaining information reference architecture, standards, and design patterns.
Building and maintaining data flow diagrams, enterprise and solution data models, and data lineage diagrams.
Reviewing and recommending data quality metrics and translate data quality issues into improvements to data ingestion and / or management.

Qualifications include:
Bachelor's degree in IT, Engineering, Computer Science, or equivalent experience.
Qlik Sense Administrator certification (preferred).
QlikView Administrator certification (preferred).
Minimum of 10 years of experience in technology, with at least 5 years in information system design and architecture.
Experience in designing and implementing big data solutions using cloud native solutions with experience in event-based architecture and data lineage tools.
Experience in designing solutions that leverage machine learning models with real-time decision engines that enable customer centric experiences.
Hands-on experience with implementing data and analytics management programs and data governance practices.
Knowledge of, and experience in, implementing data security, data privacy and data residency policies.
Understanding of common information architecture frameworks and information models.
Understanding of data science concepts, as well as MDM (Master Data Management), CDP (Customer Data Platform), BI (Business Intelligence), DWH (Data Warehouse) design and implementation techniques.
Exposure to and experience with AI/ML.
Experience with distributed management and analytics in cloud and hybrid environments.
An understanding of a variety of data access and analytics approaches including microservices and event-based architectures.
Experience with data streaming technologies.
Ability to assess rapidly changing technologies and apply them to business needs.
Business acumen and the ability to communicate to project managers, business domain stakeholders and technical staff alike.
Must have the ability to resolve issues, mitigate roadblocks, and align teams consistently and collaboratively.
Experience working with AWS, Snowflake, and modern data technologies across ingestion, transformation, and extraction/consumption.

Location

This position can be located in either US or Canada or Sweden.
