Title: Data Engineer
Description:
We are looking for a Data Engineer to join our Data & Analytics team at Volvo Car Mobility. With your help we can gain new key insights into how we can replace car ownership and contribute to helping more people move freely, meaningfully and sustainably.
The Data & Analytics team has a crucial role in setting Volvo On Demand's data-driven agenda and is responsible for the full data strategy; ranging from finding actionable insights to building data pipelines to designing machine learning-based data products. You will contribute to and learn from this talented team of data professionals in a caring, collaborative, fast-paced and exciting environment.
Our Technology
Our data platform, as well as our backend, is fully built in the cloud using Google Cloud Platform. We ingest data into our BigQuery data warehouse using Pubsub and Kubernetes-based service. Using dbt we create structured and modeled data consumable for analytical as well as data product use-cases. Visualization and analysis is done through Tableau and notebooks. We are also building a few machine learning models using Python and an MLOps-approach.
Your engagement here will include but won't be limited to:
In your role, you will work on exposing relevant data to track large and small features. Your contributions will span across the whole data stack; ranging from pure data engineering work, such as building event-based data-ingestion services, to analytics engineering where you design datasets for analysis and machine learning. You will participate in creating a scalable data platform, work with marketing and product analytics tools as well as productionize and deploy machine learning models.
As a Data Engineer, you will work closely with the product and engineering organization, representing the data perspective in a product domain and ensuring data plays an integral role in product development. Supported by experienced Data Engineers, Data Scientists and Data Analysts in the Data & Analytics team, you will work in a cross-functional and educational way. This enables you to gain insight and expertise in product development, software engineering and analytics; a combination of competencies we believe will shape you into a great Data Engineer as you grow your role and responsibilities over time.
You show experience with most of the following…
Developing data processing pipelines
Designing data models
Knowledge of software engineering fundamentals, e.g. CI/CD, testing etc.
Knowledge of an OOP-programming language as well as SQL
You are curious, eager to learn, conscientious and kind
A couple of years of experience working in a data or software engineering role
You studied Data Science, Engineering or another quantitative field such as Physics, Statistics or Mathematics
Extra awesome if you...
Experienced different data architecture paradigms, e.g. Data Lake, Data Warehouse, Data mesh
Developed machine learning models and/or deployed models using MLOps best practices
We offer a wide range of benefits designed to enhance your working life at Volvo On Demand:
Pension & compensation. You'll be looked after with Collective Agreement and ITP pensions.
Learning & innovation. Involving lunch & learns and a generous annual education budget.
Tools & equipment. From laptop to phone and more, you'll get the gear you need to do your best work.
Discounts & offers. On driving with Volvo On Demand and Hertz as well as for eating and shopping at MOOD.
Health & wellbeing. Including a 5 000 SEK annual allowance to spend, and private health insurance.
Parental support. Plenty of leave lets you take time off for what's most important.
At Volvo Car Mobility, we believe that a diverse and equal working environment is essential for the well-being and development of our co-workers. We strive for a well-balanced representation of gender and ethnic identities at every level of the organization. In this way, we hope to create an open-minded, smart, and enjoyable workplace.
Does this sound interesting to you? Then we are looking forward to your application in English!
If you have any questions, you are welcome to email us at careers@m.co. Note that due to GDPR, we do not accept applications via email.

Title: System Architect - Data & Analytics
Description:
Vill du driva modernisering, förflyttning och konsolidering i en komplex IT-miljö? Då kan vi erbjuda dig ett intressant arbete med goda utvecklingsmöjligheter i en stimulerande miljö då vi nu satsar på att förflytta hela vår affär in i framtiden.
Ditt uppdrag och ansvar som System Architect inom Data & Analytics är att utveckla och modernisera vårt IT-landskap inom ditt område. IT arbetar efter en agil filosofi där du som medarbetare och med dina kollegor i teamet får ett stort mandat i kraft av er kompetens.
Det här gör du som System Architect inom Data & Analytics
Som System Architect ansvarar du för att upprätthålla och vidareutveckla arkitekturen för Folksamgruppen inom ditt område. Du är en viktig del i arbetet med att sätta målbilder som överensstämmer med vår långsiktiga, strategiska vision samt se till att lösningarna blir kostnadseffektiva, moderna och uppfyller regulatoriska krav. Det är självklart att du känner ett stort engagemang för våra strategiska satsningar och tar ett stort ansvar för att driva arbetet framåt i nära samverkan med utvecklingsteamen, tågen samt övriga arkitekter hos oss. I rollen ingår även att hålla sig uppdaterad med trender och agera kunskapssökande inom nya innovationer och den tekniska utvecklingen inom området.
Ditt övergripande uppdrag är att utforma, dokumentera, visualisera och kommunicera förmågor inom Data & Analytics. Folksam har en lång IT-historia och har naturligtvis existerande plattformar som ska vidareutvecklas, omformas och i många fall avvecklas. En viktig del av ditt arbete kommer därför att vara att definiera transitionsarkitekturer för hur vi når målbilderna över tid och motverkar att vi duplicerar förmågor inom ditt område men också belysa om det sker på andra områden.
Specifikt för uppdraget gäller att du ska agera som fokalpunkt för teknik-, utvecklings- och plattformsfrågor inom ditt område. Du ska ha kunskap och erfarenhet både om specifika tekniker och plattformar men också om Folksams arkitekturella och agila arbetssätt. Det innefattar både kunskap om teknik och plattformsimplementation, de tekniker och standards som tjänsterna använder sig av samt kunskap om samverkande leverantörer och avtal för att leverera dessa.
Du samverkar tätt med andra arkitekter, utvecklare och affärsintressenter i operativa, taktiska och strategiska frågeställningar kring landskapet samt bär ”teknikfanan” i strategisk/taktisk dialog med leverantörer. Du ansvarar för att rekommendera vägval baserat på ekonomi, kompetens, teknikval och implementationssätt samt lämpliga och effektiva leveransmodeller.
Du ansvarar för de teknikplattformar som stöttar Folksamgruppens behov inom data och analys, såsom Business Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Warehousing och Masterdata men också underliggande infrastruktur i molnet där vi arbetar med infrastruktur som kod. Arkitektur, teknik och modern analysplattform ska stötta förflyttning mot effektivare informationsförsörjning som leder till ett mer datadrivet bolag samt snabbare insikter.
Är du den vi söker?
Vi söker dig som har flerårig erfarenhet av arkitekturarbete inom data & analytics i komplexa organisationer. Vi jobbar med Microsoft Azure och det är därför särskilt önskvärt om du har erfarenhet av det området, och helst har arbetat inom Data & Analytics i Azure. Du har tidigare erfarenhet inom data science, data engineering, ETL-utveckling, analys och rapportering och agila arbetssätt. Har du dessutom erfarenhet som chef eller ledare ser vi det som meriterande.
Som person ser vi att du är kreativ, resultatinriktad och övertygad om att det alltid finns lösningar på komplexa problem. Du är ansvarstagande och har hög förmåga att driva frågor själv. Du involverar och vägleder andra och samarbetar gärna tvärfunktionellt. Vidare skapar du förtroende genom bemötande och kunskap och ser ständigt lärande som en självklarhet.
Vill du vara med och påverka Folksams förflyttning till molnet och driva vår digitaliseringsresa framåt i ett företag med stort hjärta där IT är högt på agendan så har du chansen nu. Vi lovar dig att det kommer bli både lärorikt och spännande!
Utvecklas tillsammans med oss
Folksam är ett kundägt företag med stort fokus på hållbarhetsfrågor. Vi har många roliga, utvecklande jobb och bra förmåner. Vi tror på ett hållbart arbetsliv och hos oss har du goda chanser till en spännande karriär. Vi erbjuder flexibilitet att varva arbete på kontoret och hemifrån utifrån verksamhetens behov. Våra trevliga kontor runt om i landet ger mötesplatser för samarbete, lärande och en gemensam kultur – tillsammans skapar vi engagemang och kraft framåt! På folksam.se/jobb-och-karriar kan du läsa mer och se filmer om hur det är att jobba på Folksam.
Så söker du jobbet
Välkommen med din ansökan så fort som möjligt men senast 20 februari 2023.
För mer information om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande chef Jacob Karmehag, 072-468 71 83 eller Henrik Nose 070-831 52 82.
Fackliga representanter: Forena Morgan Svensson, 073-423 59 12, Akademikerföreningen Per Hansson 070-831 60 67 och Handels Mikael Carlsson 070-831 51 32.
Folksamgruppen erbjuder försäkringar och långsiktigt sparande som skapar trygghet i livets alla skeden. Vi är cirka 4 000 medarbetare och vår vision är att våra kunder ska känna sig trygga i en hållbar värld. Vi engagerar oss i det våra kunder bryr sig om och är måna om att de är rätt försäkrade.

Title: Computer Vision - Internship/Project Assistance/Master...
Description:
ManoMotion is looking for passionate and innovative interns/project assistants or master thesis students in Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Media Technology, Interaction Design or related areas. The main focus will be on research and development challenges related to 3D hand tracking and gesture analysis for smart devices and mobile platforms.
About ManoMotion:
ManoMotion is a Deep Tech company based in Stockholm, Sweden. We are a diverse team of Computer Vision and Machine Learning Scientists and creative software engineers, specialists in stretching the borders of what is technically possible to decipher from a camera. ManoMotion brings unparalleled intuition in human-machine interactions, refined through more than 10 years of research in gesture technology with a number of inventions and international awards. We have developed a core technology framework to achieve precise hand tracking and gesture recognition in 3D-space simply using a regular camera available on any smart device!
Required skills
Master degree or equivalent level of experience in Machine Learning, Computer Vision, Data Science, Interaction Design, Media Technology or related areas.
Strong theoretical knowledge in Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Image Analysis.
Experience in development of Computer Vision solutions.
Good coding skills and knowledge of C++/Python/OpenCV.
Previous experience of using deep learning tools and frameworks such as TensorFlow and Keras.
Self-driven problem solver with a strong sense of teamwork.
Strong Advantages
Industry experience in the field of computer vision applications.
Previous experience in mobile development (iOS/Androis/Unity)
Familiar with agile software development.
Publications in the field of computer vision/machine learning.

Title: Analytiker med intresse för komplexa system
Description:
Vi på Digital Tvilling bygger representationer av komplexa system som ser ut och beter sig som verkligheten. Detta kan vara transportsystem, energisystem eller livsmedel. Eller något helt annat.
Vi söker nu analytiker till att jobba inom vårt Produktutveckling & Analys-team. Din bakgrund är sannolikt inom datavetenskap, data-science, data-engineering, statistik, matematik eller något närbesläktat.
Vi tror att du har intresse, erfarenhet och kunskap inom något, några eller alla av dessa områden:
Tekniker vi arbetar bland annat med är PostgreSQL/Postgis/Timescale, Neo4j och Tableau
Visualisering och analys av geospatial data och tidsserier
Analys av data kring transportsystem och logistiksystem
Intresse kring komplexa nätverk, grafteori, sociotekniska system, systemdynamik och besläktade områden
Kunskap i programmering i exempelvis R, Python, Java eller liknande är meriterande men inte ett krav
Svenska/norska och engelska i tal och skrift
Vi tror att du antingen har arbetat ett antal år med ovan tekniker eller har en relativt färsk examen och vill fördjupa och bygga dina kunskaper.
Du kommer att arbeta med att utveckla vår plattform tillsammans med vårt team och våra kunder och arbetet består av en kombination av produktutveckling och kundleveranser.
Vi är flexibla som arbetsgivare och tillhandahåller kontor om du vill ha det, men vi tror även på att jobba på distans vid rätt förutsättningar. Majoriteten av bolaget sitter i Stockholm men du kan vara placerad där det fungerar bäst för dig. Vi värderar resultat mer än tid på kontoret. Visst resande kan ske inom tjänsten.

Title: Master Data Management (MDM) experter
Description:
Till flera nya projekt till våren söker vi nu erfarna konsulter inom MDM – Master Data management. För dessa spännande projekt behöver vi stärka upp vårt MDM-team med både utvecklare, projektledare och Business Analysts.
Hos oss arbetar några av Nordens främsta experter inom Data, Analytics & AI, vilket ger oss bästa möjliga förutsättningar att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas på sin resa mot ett datadrivet beslutsfattande.
Vi bistår våra uppdragsgivare med datadriven affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling hela vägen från strategiska vägval till implementerad lösning och realiserad nytta.
Hos oss är medarbetarnas utrymme att utvecklas stort och kulturen präglas av frihet under ansvar. För dig som lockas av att vara med i Sveriges vassaste team inom Data, Analytics och AI, är detta ett jobb med framtidsmöjligheter för dig.
Mer om oss:
Capgemini Insights & Data, är Nordens ledare inom Data, AI och Analytics. Vi är över 300 anställda, fördelade på våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö och Helsingborg. Våra tjänster innefattar konsultverksamhet inom Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services och Solution Services. Många av marknadens främsta experter arbetar hos oss, vilket ger oss utmärkta förutsättningar att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas i sin resa mot datadrivna beslut. Vår position på den nordiska marknaden ger oss möjlighet att verkligen göra skillnad för våra kunder, och att erbjuda alltifrån lokala projekt till större globala transformationsprojekt.
Vem du är:
Vi söker nu dig som har flera års erfarenhet inom området MDM – Master Data Management i roller som utvecklare, projektledare och/eller Business Analyst. Du har erfarenhet ifrån ett antal olika MDM projekt och du är van att arbeta med kunder i olika branscher och inom olika funktioner.
Du har gärna en bakgrund som Data Steward med helhetssyn och bred kunskap inom en verksamhets masterdatahantering
Vi ser gärna att du har erfarenhet av att arbeta med olika MDM verktyg, där minst ett av dom är Profisee eller Informatica. Vi tror även att du har lång erfarenhet av att arbeta med SQL.
Det är viktigt att du är analytisk, lösningsorienterad och nyfiken, att du har en god samarbetsförmåga samt lätt för att kommunicera. Du har relevant högskoleutbildning och du kan svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift.

Title: Backend Developer
Description:
Description
The way we use water today is not sustainable. We’re here to change that. Working at Orbital means using innovation, teamwork and passion to help address one of the world’s most pressing challenges. We need to stop wasting water, and the best way to do that is to use less to begin with. To get people on board, we’ve got to do it in a way that doesn’t compromise ease-of-use and comfort. That’s your job in a nutshell. Come join a diverse team of experts, bring your skills and let’s get to work!
The idea was born in an academic project in collaboration with NASA, and then developed into a working product that enables you to shower in full comfort saving up to 90% compared to traditional showers, and 80% of the energy consumed to heat the water. Orbital Systems was founded by Mehrdad Mahdjoubi in 2012 and is backed by leading investors including Skype founder Niklas Zennström, and leaders from Tesla, Sony, H&M and more.
The Role
We’re looking for our next rockstar developer to join the team. You’re a skilled backend developer that loves writing clean code and is an expert in Javascript (Typescript).
Our backend stack is serverless and written in Node.js and Python. Everything is hosted on AWS and deployed with CI/CD-pipelines.
Our frontend stack is React-based using next.js for web apps and react-native for our Android/iOS app. Some experience and desire to contribute on the frontend when needed is a big plus.
At ORBITAL SYSTEMS, you will participate in design, development, and implementation of new features on our cloud platform. You will identify and drive IoT platform utilisation service improvements and also participate in the analysis, usability and the engagement model of the IoT platform. Continuing to remain current on the latest IoT technology is key for this role, and you will work with product management and engineering on a daily basis in order to define requirements and development, taking ownership of multiple systems from development to deployment.

Requirements
You have a real desire and aptitude to work in a fast-paced growth environment and be part of a unique journey. To succeed, you need to have a proven track record of building high-quality and efficient applications.
Essential skills and experience
3+ years of commercial software engineering experience in a fast-paced environment
Strong experience of building customer facing products on the cloud such as AWS and familiar with cloud related technologies
Excellent debugging and problem solving skills
Great English communication skills (written and speaking)
Confidence in own ideas while being open for discussion with others
Experience with Git and the Github workflow
Knowledge of Clean Code practices
Comfort with creating and consuming web based REST APIs
Solid understanding of NoSQL databases
Experience of creating services with scalability, high availability, high security and reliability in mind
Nice to have
Startup & Agile development experience
Experience working with MQTT or similar IoT communication protocols
Experience building and maintaining Jamstack applications using JavaScript/TypeScript and React
Interest in design and experience developing applications with a rich and innovative user experience
Interest in the possibilities and challenges of physical product development
Interest in data science
Benefits
You will have the opportunity to be part of something unique, and build a rapidly scaling business from the ground up. We also offer:
Career development within a fast-growing organization
Generous equity options – own the success you help create
A company where everyone knows why they get out of bed in the mornings
If you are interested to join the movement and ready to make a difference in how we are using water in the world, please send in your CV (and an optional Cover Letter).
Apply for this job

Title: Data Engineer to Vetfamily
Description:
Do you have a passion for well-structured data pipelines and want to be responsible for developing and maintaining our data warehouse?
Vimian is a global and diversified group of innovation-driven companies with a shared passion for making a positive impact through improving animal health. Together we put science, technology and our customer’s needs at the centre of everything we do to deliver effective solutions to veterinary professionals, labs and pet owners around the world.
We are looking for a self-driven, structured Data Warehouse Engineer to join our IT & BI team and lead the work in extending the Financial Data Warehouse into an insight generating business platform. We are looking for candidates with understanding of ERP systems and Financial Book Keeping and having a track record of operating system with a multitude of sources. The right candidate will find an exciting role leading a highly prioritized project within the financially stable and fast growing international Vimian Group.

What you will do:
Take over ownership of the established, well architectured and documented data warehouse platform which runs on Azure with Data factory, Synapse and powerBI.
Ensure the integrity of the dataware house architecture as you extend it with additional sources of data.
Continuously extend the pipelines as new companies are acquired and onboarded.
Jointly with the rest of the powerBI team, collaborate with Group Management, Finance, and operations to provide data analysis to answer business questions.
Ensure the DWH transforms the data into usable and presentable insight.
Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure the established data definitions match their expectations.
With us, you will be leading highly prioritized projects to spread data accessibility and usage through data pipelines across the Vimian Group.
Ensure a stable and reliable DWH that can deliver key financial data even during critical reporting periods.


Is this you?
Structured and self motivated.
Ability to maintain architecture while growing features and extending pipelines.
Bachelor or Master’s degree in Computer Science or Data science.
4+ years data engineering experience as a BI developer or software engineer.
Experience with Azure Synapse, Azure Devops, Azure Data factory powerBI. Or extensive experience with similar tools and a willingness and ability to quickly learn new tools.
Expert knowledge of SQL, Cloud Hosted Data warehouse Management.
Scripting knowledge.

Title: Data Engineer (Engagement team)
Description:
Pushing boundaries to achieve a sustainable future
The world is dealing with an environmental crisis and energy crisis, and we, as Vargas Holding’s latest venture, are actively creating a sustainable future. We provide renewable energy solutions to everyday homes to help them cut their dependency on oil and gas, electrify their energy consumption, and to control their energy bill. To solve the climate and energy crisis, we are at the forefront of creating innovative solutions that accelerate the creation of smart and sustainable homes.
Heating alone represents some 15% of the EU's CO2 emissions and switching to a sustainable energy solution is by far the easiest way for a household to make a real impact. That's why we are dedicated to developing solutions that not only combat these crises and create sustainable homes but also empower homeowners to take control of their energy consumption and save money on their energy bills.
Our goal is to cut homeowners’ dependency on fossil fuels and help them transition to clean, renewable energy sources. We make it possible for everyone to combat the climate crisis. With a firm belief in the power of innovation and technology, we build solutions for today’s challenges, and for those of tomorrow – for current and our next generations. By transforming local energy consumption, we will create a global transformation.
We are passionate about making a positive impact on the world, and we believe that by creating smart and sustainable homes, we can do just that. We hope you will join us in this important work as we strive to make a difference in the fight against the climate crisis.

About the role
We are expanding our Engagement team where we focus on creating an engaging experience for our customers when they have their energy solution installed at home. We are looking for somebody who can help us create the data structures and models, the operational environment we need to optimize our data analytics and visualization for our users.
You will be responsible for designing and implementing data structures and pipelines to support data-driven features and capabilities for our software application. You will work closely with cross-functional teams including product management, data science, and engineering to understand data requirements and ensure that data is properly collected, cleansed, transformed, stored and served for use in data-driven products and features.
Your other responsibilities include:
Assist with the design, setup, maintenance and support of data pipelines and structures
Participate in the design and development of data-driven products and features
Collaborate with team members to troubleshoot and resolve data-related issues

Who are you
From a technical perspective we would like you to have:
2-3 YoE as a data engineer
Strong understanding of data engineering concepts
Experience working with a variety of data sources and technologies
Experience with data cleansing and transformation, ETL pipelines
Comfort working with large and complex datasets
Familiarity with SQL and other database querying languages
We would even appreciate it if you have some experience with/knowledge of some of the following:
Familiarity with other programming languages such as Java, Kotlin or Python
As a person we would like you to be:
High ambition, initiative, and entrepreneurial mindset (self-starter)
A personality who thrives in an ever-changing environment and can create structure from the ground up
Fast-moving and solution-oriented
Analytical skills

What we offer
Besides a competitive salary and secondary benefits, we offer the opportunity to build a global company and product with true environmental impact. Our team is led by top engineers from IKEA, Volvo, Scania, Viaplay, and Kry, bringing a wealth of experience and expertise to the table.
As a member of our team, you'll have the chance to be a part of a fast-moving growth journey with far-reaching learning and development opportunities. You'll have the chance to work with some of the most talented and innovative professionals in the industry, dedicated to making a positive impact on the world through our products and services. You'll be able to contribute to the development of cutting-edge technology that has the potential to make a significant positive impact on the world.
In addition to the opportunity to contribute to a meaningful and impactful company, you'll also have access to ongoing learning and development opportunities to help you grow both personally and professionally. We believe that our team is our greatest asset, and we are committed to fostering a supportive and inclusive culture that empowers our employees to reach their full potential.
Whether you're an experienced professional or just starting out in your career, we believe that everyone has the potential to make a meaningful contribution to our mission. So, if you're passionate about building a better future and want to be a part of something special, we'd love to have you join us. So, come and join our team and be a part of building a truly global company with a product that makes a real difference in the world.
Don't hesitate and send us your application today! If you have any questions regarding applications or else, contact me at rolf.kusch@vargasholding.se

Title: Data Engineer to Data Platform and Innovation team
Description:
Are you a passionate Data Engineer with great organizational and communication skills?
We, at Dustin, are now looking for Data Engineers with varied experience levels who have a strong passion to develop their career in the field, make an impact and are curious to experience how it is working with a leading online based IT partner.
Data Engineer to Data Platform and Innovation team
You will be part of the central platform team to build best practice, sharing knowledge as well as delivering main components to the agile value streams teams. The responsibility of the team consists of creating the common building blocks that enables other teams to move faster, this could be related to data ingestion, data pipelines, data integrations, CI/CD pipelines and provide best practice.
The central team will also host demos across agile teams. Moreover, the team will also do exploratory work and make proof of concepts together with the agile team or together with different parts of business to explore new emerging techs or ways of working. Our stack is focused on Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Factory and Databricks. Python and SQL are the main languages.
We are a tight team that emphasizes testing new things and learning from each other. Being a part of this team; you get the right environment to adopt and continue the self-driven independent approach to test and succeed with a constant access to guidance as and when required. We believe in continually sharing knowledge and believe that your growth with us should not be limited to the individual projects you take.
What you get
Opportunity to make a difference; impart knowledge among teammates, feeding crucial data to analysts, decision-making and playing a pivotal role in organization’s success
Opportunity to build data solutions with real impact using state-of-the-art tools and platforms.
Opportunity to learn and develop within areas outside of your core competence such as solution architecture, data science and project management.
Working in a great, highly skilled team with a “win as a team” attitude and inclusive culture.
Digital First: We believe in flexibility and that we should work from where we are the most effective.
Collective agreements and wellness grants are examples of benefits.
What you have
3+ years of experience from a similar role.
You know SQL and Python, have experience with Spark, ETL, DevOps practices and CI/CD when it comes to data.
3+ years of hands-on experience of cloud data platforms such as Azure Data Lake, Google BigQuery, Snowflake or similar
Problem solving mindset.
Good presentation, organisational and communication skills with fluency in English.
Passion for People & Technology
Recruitment Process
We want a good match! If needed, we will perform multiple interviews, and possibly a case study test.
If you have any questions regarding the position, please contact the recruiter by email at karishma.sindhu@dustin.se or recruiting manager for this role Marcel Beerden, Team Manager, Data & Insights at marcel.beerden@dustin.com.

Title: Data Scientist (Senior level) - Games
Description:
As a Data Scientist in the data science team at Embark you will be a game maker in a small team focused on supporting and leading the analytical efforts of a PVP game and delivering insights to our game team.
The Data Science team at Embark is a small team focused on making sure we have data and analysis supporting game design and development, as well as a data model and reports to serve the rest of the business.
You’ll be an integral part of a highly creative game team and together you’ll create and improve the high-quality, polished experiences we want to provide to our players. At Embark we believe in creating smaller teams of well-aligned experts that can be trusted to create games and keep them running. Some of the technologies we use to make all of those things are Python and BigQuery.

Example of responsibilities
Collaborate and work closely with game designers and business stakeholders.
Research and develop metrics and performance indicators
Extract, analyze and communicate insights from gameplay data
Apply machine learning models to better understand our players
Design telemetry logging
Communicate results clearly and concisely to all the business stakeholders
We would love if you have some of the following
Experience working with either Hadoop, BigQuery, Snowflake
Strong Programming skills in Python or R
Deep knowledge of complex SQL
Experience in predictive modeling and analysis over large datasets
Experience in building dashboards and reports using tools such as rshiny/streamlit/jupyter notebooks etc
Experience in making ETLs and data pipelines
Great written and verbal communication and presentation skills in English
Experience or interest in games


At Embark we offer competitive salaries, passionate colleagues to share knowledge with and much more, but most of all we invite you to take part of a journey into the unknown, to build creative, surprising and beautiful experiences together.
We welcome game makers of all sex, class, colour, age, gender identity, education, religion, opinion, culture, nation of origin, language, sexual orientation, shape, size, and ability.
Did we leave anyone out? Well, we welcome you, too! We think that the gaming industry is made better when everyone has a seat at the table. Be yourself at Embark and make games while doing so. Please apply with confidence. We can’t wait to hear from you (in English)!
If this role doesn't quite match what you're looking for, feel free to apply to us via our "Open Application."

Title: PHP Developer | Web shop
Description:
PHP Developer | Web shop
THE OPPORTUNITY
At Boozt we work in small cross functional teams of up to six developers in a big community. In total we are 176 developers spread across 5 locations. At Boozt, a high standard of code is important, which we manage through the latest technology stacks, internal code reviews and sharing knowledge through hackathons, conferences and weekly talks. Here we love to develop, not only the code but also ourselves as developers.
We are now looking for developers to strengthen the teams working with our web shop. This is an opportunity for you that wants to be a part of one of our most technical teams at Boozt. The team's focus is to work with big data to enable a fast and efficient web shop.
OUR TECH STACK
All our systems are deployed in the Google Cloud Platform. We have adopted Terraform for all the configuration and management of the infrastructure, no manual ad-hoc changes are being done. We are using a mix of Compute Engine, App Engine, Cloud Functions, and Kubernetes to deploy our systems, depending on their needs and characteristics. Current plan is to go more towards Kubernetes, we are in the process of containerizing more of our applications. Cloudflare is being used for CDN, authentication, and canary deployments among other things.
The majority of our systems are written in PHP using the Symfony framework. Among other languages that we are using are Elixir, Go, Python, TypeScript, Kotlin, Swift. For the data layer we have a mix of MySQL, Redis, Elasticsearch, MongoDB, Manticore. We try to be pragmatic and pick the technology that suits us best for the specific task. Cross-system communication is happening over Google Pub/Sub and RabbitMQ.
Observability is something we put a lot of focus on. We are actively monitoring the health of our infrastructure and applications using Datadog. We use it to get a good overview of the errors, make sure that deployments are not affecting performance, make sure that the SLOs are not over the limit, investigate and collaborate during major outages.
WHAT YOU WILL DO
Development and maintenance in PHP, using the Symfony framework.
Automate manual tasks to help the business users do their everyday work.
Update and improve new and existing technologies to ensure high system performance.
Implement new features and functions needed for the company.
Multiple deployments a day due to continuous integration and an agile workflow.
You will interact with business units to help determine scopes, plan and specify projects.
Maintaining and improving system integrations using asynchronous messaging (RabbitMQ and Google Pub/Sub and various APIs).
YOUR PROFILE
At least 3 years work experience with PHP development.
Experience from working with PHP frameworks, Symfony is a plus.
Experience in working closely with other business units in order to understand the needs and improve the system.
BS or MS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field desirable.
Fluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered).
Meritorious with enterprise system knowledge.
Welcome to apply for the position!
BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor
A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Är byggandet av data pipelines din grej? Vi söker dig som är duktig på att bygga ramverk för att andra skall kunna analysera data och du förstår även vikten av datadriven utveckling för att skapa framtidens produkter och tjänster.
Din framtida utmaning
Just nu ser vi ett uppsving i antalet utmaningar som är kopplade till datahantering. Datainsamlingen i sig är oftast straight-forward, och utmaningen ligger således i att förädla datamängden och göra den användbar. Det kan handla om allt från att extrahera, städa, sortera, och filtrera data till att använda statistiska verktyg för att hitta nya samband och visualisera detta med hjälp av BI-system. Din uppgift blir att förse övriga organisationen med rätt förutsättningar att kunna jobba datadrivet i sin utveckling.
Den du är idag
Som person är du engagerad, analytisk, och strävar efter att leverera ditt bästa resultat varje gång. Du är kreativ och nyfiken inför uppdragets behov och kan snabbt anpassa dig till olika situationer. Du tycker att det är spännande när allting inte är bestämt på förhand och sporras av att få sätta dig in i nya sammanhang. Du har fenomenal fingertoppskänsla och har förståelse för verksamhetens behov, för att kunna hitta den rätta lösningen för att komma framåt. Du är social och gillar att arbeta i team och ser spännande utmaningar i de möjligheter som erbjuds.
Krav
Utbildningsbakgrund inom Data, Fysik, Teknisk Matematik eller Statistik
Givetvis kan du programmera
Vi söker dig som kan åtminstone ett av nedan koncept
AWS, GCP, Azure
Azure-moduler såsom Data Factory/Event Hub/Service Bus
Spark, Hadoop
Power BI, SAS
Andra koncept
Vi ser med intresse på om du har något av följande erfarenheter med dig
Erfarenhet av dataanalys, data science
Erfarenhet av att arbeta agilt
Ansökan
Om du är intresserad av att bli en del av vår gemenskap på Infotiv så tycker vi att du ska ansöka till oss! Vi önskar höra mer om:
Dina erfarenheter; vad du har gjort tidigare i livet och vad du önskar göra framöver
Vem du är utanför arbetet
Eventuellt några rader om vad som gör dig till just den du är
Vilka vi är
Infotiv TechDev består idag av 70 ingenjörer, där våra uppdrag täcker alla aspekter av mjukvaruutvecklingsprocessen, från koncept och design till implementation och slutverifiering. Vi värdesätter ett öppet klimat och stöttar våra ambitiösa medarbetare. Som teknikkonsult hos Infotiv är man aldrig ensam och man har flertalet aktiviteter att engagera sig i, både kompetensbyggande och sociala.
Som teknikkonsult på Infotiv är du en del av ett företag som vårdar människorna som arbetar här. Företaget karaktäriseras av korta beslutsvägar och en familjär atmosfär, vilket gör att din närmaste chef har stora möjligheter att själv bestämma. Vi vet vad uppdragen går ut på, vilka utmaningar som finns och vilka egenskaper som uppskattas av uppdragsgivaren. Ledorden varmt hjärta, skarp hjärna genomsyrar vår organisation och samtliga våra medarbetare. Givetvis har vi bra lön och kollektivavtal.
Låter detta intressant, så tveka inte att ansöka redan idag. Vi genomför intervjuer löpande och tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas innan sista ansökningsdatum. Vi hoppas att du vill vara med och växa med oss!

Title: Technical Sales Engineer - Summer internship (Sweden)
Description:
Internship dates: 15th June – 4th August 2023

Location: Sweden (Internship to be hybrid)


What You’ll Do
This position provides you with meaningful work that directly affects your assigned sales engineering team. During the summer, you will gain exposure to Cisco technology, sales and the opportunity to network and learn from top engineering leaders within the organisation.
Working with Sales Engineering to problem solve and work with customers
Demos and Programming script-based development tools
Ability to tackle stretch projects and be creative individually in a team environment



Who You'll Work With
At Cisco, we are dedicated to attracting, developing, and retaining top early university talent to shape our future, and we want you! You will learn, gain sales experience and grow within Cisco. Work with sales engineer leaders to make an impact on the business while getting exposure to our executives and sales organisation. Do you want to become Cisco's next generation of sales leaders through an accelerated early in career development path? Join us and explore how Cisco changes the way the world works, lives, plays, and learns.



Who You Are
Pursuing a BS or MS degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Data Science, Mathematics, Physics, or other equivalent degree in a technical discipline is required (an emphasis on software design practices preferred) set to graduate December 2023 – July 2024

Excellent in presentation skills as well as written and verbal communication skills
You have a real passion for technology
You have application centric skills
You are a creative thinker and problem solver
Strong skills: Researching, influencing, organisation, adaptability, flexibility, and highly self-motivated
Proven leadership and interpersonal skills, teamwork, ability to work in collaborative environment - all with a positive attitude
Fluent in English (written and verbal)
Must be able to legally live and work in the country for which you're applying, without visa support or sponsorship. (student visas or visas obtained on your own are not applicable for the program.)



Why Cisco
#WeAreCisco, where each person is unique, but we bring our talents to work as a team and make a difference. Here’s how we do it.
We embrace digital, and help our customers implement change in their digital businesses. Some may think we’re “old” (30 years strong!) and only about hardware, but we’re also a software company. And a security company. A blockchain company. An AI/Machine Learning company. We even invented an intuitive network that adapts, predicts, learns and protects. No other company can do what we do – you can’t put us in a box!
But “Digital Transformation” is an empty buzz phrase without a culture that allows for innovation, creativity, and yes, even failure (if you learn from it).

Message to applicants applying to work in the U.S.:
When available, the salary range posted for this position reflects the projected hiring range for new hire salaries in U.S. locations. For non-sales roles, the hiring ranges reflect base salary and do not include bonuses, equity, or benefits. Hiring ranges for sales positions include base and incentive target, and do not include equity or benefits. Individual pay is determined by the candidate's hiring location and additional factors, including but not limited to skillset, experience, and relevant education, certifications or training. Applicants may not be eligible for the full salary range based on their U.S. hiring location. The recruiter can share more details about compensation for the role in your location during the hiring process.

Title: Senior Data Architect
Description:
Why Avaus?
We are the leading marketing and sales transformation partner in the Nordics! We are 120 colleagues located at our offices in Helsinki, Stockholm, Munich, Milan and Gdansk. As a company, we have more than 15 years of experience in data-driven marketing and sales in large organizations across B2C & B2B industries.
Our vision is to become the leading actionable marketing data-asset provider in Europe by 2025. We believe that to survive, companies need to invest heavily in capabilities related to intelligence & AI, customer experience, personalisation and change management. Our mission is to foster customer-centric companies equipped to grow and face the future. Our own future growth is heavily driven by activating data and analytics for our clients.
The Team
The market is shifting faster than ever and to keep up, companies need to invest in their data capabilities to deliver relevant and tailored content and information fit to your and your customers’ needs. This is where we come in as engineers. By utilizing the latest, leading cloud technologies combined with machine learning, we build scalable, future proof data solutions, to achieve this goal.
As a new member of our Data Engineering team, your responsibilities involve design and development of varieties of data processing solutions. The team provides the technical backbone needed for a data-driven and personalized customer experience. At Avaus you will find a collaborative environment with lots of personal responsibility and freedom where your problem solving abilities and eagerness to learn new technologies will flourish. Here you will take ownership and drive conversations and tasks on your own initiative. We are a social crew and enjoy working closely together and learning from one another.

The role
As a Data Engineer you will work in multidisciplinary client teams. You will work in an Agile environment where you have a client-facing role and work in close collaboration with our clients' business and technical stakeholders. You will use your patented passion to capture and understand the requirements of complex data solutions. Effectiveness in a collaborative environment and valuing teamwork is one of the keys to this role.You will most likely be doing some of these things also:
Be part of feature development, from planning all the way through to test and delivery
Working closely together with our data science team in delivering machine learning solutions by using the latest in technology
Be part of Avaus internal development initiatives, where we set new standards in how we deliver to our clients
Security and privacy measures
Who are you?
We're looking for a person with a passion for technology and data. You understand the need for and importance of continuous delivery and what's required. You have prioritizing elegance and simplicity when writing code. People describe you as a team-player and you have the ability to create valuable relationships. You have a strong sense of ownership and want to be part of our journey! Beside your personality, we would also like you to have:
Academic Bachelor's degree, e.g computer science, technology or similar
Extensive experience in building and designing customer data solutions on one of the three big cloud platforms. E.g GCP, AWS or Azure, GCP in particular
Expert in SQL and data modelling
Extensive experience of concepts and building continuous integration/deployment solutions and Infrastructure as code
Extensive experience with the concept of microservices and how to build such architectures
Experience in implementing security and privacy best practices, knowledge in how to deliver GDPR-compliant solutions
Expert in one or more programming languages like Python or Java
Experience in consulting
Experience in containers and container-based solutions
Fluent in English
Practical information:
This is a permanent position with a 6 months’ probation period, based at our Stockholm office at Katarinavägen 17. Starting date as soon as possible or by agreement. We offer a hybrid remote workplace and you will report to Team Lead, Anthon Ytterell.
Already feel like one of us? Send your applications in English as soon as possible, but no later than 2023-02-28. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Anthon. Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page.
We look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Strategic Advisor within Data & AI
Description:
As a Strategic Advisor, you will join our team of leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers make the right decisions and give them a solid foundation to succeed on their journey towards becoming data driven. Capgemini Insights & Data is the Nordic market leader in Data & Analytics.
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data has a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
With our strong track record as the Nordic market leader in Data & Analytics, you will be able to leverage our expertise and resources to deliver high-impact solutions to our clients. With us you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of clients and industries, together with amazing colleagues.
Are you a strategic thinker with a passion for data and artificial intelligence? Do you thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment? If so, we want you to join our team as a Strategic Advisor within Data & AI! As a Strategic Advisor, you will be responsible for providing expert guidance and recommendations to our clients on how to leverage data and AI to achieve their business goals. You will work closely with our clients to understand their needs and challenges and use your strategic thinking skills to develop tailored solutions that drive results.
To be successful in this role, you will need to have a strong background in business as well as data and AI. We equally value if you come from either a solid technical background or a more business-oriented role, you thrive in the center of business and technology. You also need excellent communication and relationship-building skills. Previous experience from a consulting or advisory role is a strong advantage.
As a Strategic Advisor, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing Data & AI Solutions.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients on how to use Data & Analytics to align with the business strategy and achieve business goals.
Guiding our clients in the decision making of how to develop their data strategies to align with the business strategy.
Driving initiatives to create the foundation within data & AI.
Driving initiatives to create a data driven organization.
Working with stakeholder management, change management etc.
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Advisory, Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
More information about life at Insights & Data: https://capgemini-insights-dat...
Who You Are
What we are looking for:
You are a business-oriented person with a strong understanding on what makes organizations work and businesses tick.
You have experience on working with strategy development, objective setting, follow up etc.
You have hands on experience of developing data strategies for organizations.
Hands on experience on how to organize work within the data & analytics field for different kinds of businesses.
Familiar with data management, data security, and access control in the cloud.
People with experience from one or more business domains, for example finance, retail, industry, services, telecom, public, energy etc.
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills as well as stakeholder management.
Driven, proactive individuals who are eager to make a positive impact on our clients and our business.
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience in architecting and designing data solutions using trade-off analysis
Knowledge of different information architecture patterns
Experience on how to work with governance and master data within the data & analytics field.

Title: CEO for MainlyAI
Description:
MainlyAI is a Sweden and US-based deeptech start-up founded in 2020 that offers a platform-as-a-service for AI development, execution and sharing. The company is well funded through governmental and private investments and has 5 employees today. We are looking for you to take control for its day-to-day operations and long-term strategies and execution.

What will you do:
Develop and drive Sales as well as Fundraising strategies & activities for MainlyAI
Represent MainlyAI in customer and investors’ dialogues
Act as a Product Owner for MainlyAI’s Platform-as-a-Service, MIRANDA, and guide the technical development team with respect to new features and feature prioritisation
Develop the company in accordance with the strategies decided by the board of directors
Drive development of organization and business processes of the company
Ensure fulfilment of ongoing project commitments
Your Must-have qualifications:
MSc or PhD in computer science, engineering or similar
Experience in running start-ups and raising venture capital
Proven experience in business development
5+ years of experience in running large-scale software projects
Experience with people leadership
Strong communication skills
Your Good-to-have qualifications:
Artificial Intelligence/Data Science knowledge
Experience in Platform-as-a-Service sales
Experience in two-sided business models
Experience from healthcare/medtech/biotech domain
Experience from product management
Proven innovation skills (e.g. in form of patents or publications)
Contact:
If you think you can be the new CEO for MainlyAI please reach out to Cecilia Lantz on cecilia.lantz@netwrk.se

Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
About Validio
Validio is the next generation data quality and reliability company. Our platform monitors and validates both data in motion and data at rest on datapoint and pipeline metadata level. Validio’s mission is to eliminate bad data and enable organizations to be data-driven with confidence. We work with modern data teams and data innovators, who push daily what they can do with data to improve their businesses, customer experience, services and products.

Here you will work with a senior team of data and machine learning professionals with backgrounds from renowned research institutions, leading startups, and established tech companies. Even though several members of our team have PhDs, we have all been working in industry and place an emphasis on cutting through the hype and building things that actually work and deliver real business value.
About the role
We are looking for a Senior Data Scientist to join our team and help us push beyond what is currently possible in the area of data quality. Your daily responsibilities will include:
Driving data science projects end to end, starting from a business problem, building hypotheses for a solution, defining data requirements, creating a prototype, implementing it into production, and measuring the business impact
Contribute to the development of production-grade models, ensuring reliability and scalability, for e.g. predictions, optimization and anomaly detection
Make improvements and maintain our data science ecosystem, which consists of both deployed models as well as the infrastructure required to support them
Contribute to the discussion related to tech-stack choices, improving team ways of working and prioritizing between problems and projects
We believe you are/have
To succeed in this role we believe that you have a master's degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics or a related quantitative field and at least 5 years of experience in a similar role (or convince us that you have a similar level of expertise)
You also are/have:
A proven history of building and deploying Data Science solutions in production, preferably for different use cases.
Previous experience in forecasting, predictive modeling, optimization and computer vision are meriting
Expertise in time-series analysis, anomaly detection, and unsupervised methods
Sense of urgency, ownership mindset, and product intuition
Previous experience in a fast-moving organization and approaching complex problems with iterative pragmatic solutions
Knowledge of tooling related to: Machine Learning, cloud solutions, orchestration and data processing.
Professional working proficiency in English, Swedish is not required
Here at Validio we offer you the chance to be part of something truly amazing and with a world class team, there is no limit to what we can achieve together. We promise that you will be challenged, pushed to develop your skill set and get the opportunity to work alongside amazing and smart colleagues from all over the world on our mission to eliminate bad data.
For now begin your journey with us by clicking "Apply" below. We cannot wait to meet you!

Title: Finnish Speaking Customer Service Agent
Description:
Customer Service Agent - Finland
THE OPPORTUNITY
Do you have an interest in fashion, see solutions rather than problems and always strive to provide service at a top level? Then this opportunity might be the one for you.
Do you also value a dynamic and international work environment, fun and knowledgeable colleagues as well as a lot of internal career opportunities, then apply and get the chance to join our amazing Customer Service Team.
As our new Customer Service Agent you will join a team, where you together will work towards providing world class service to our customers.

WHAT YOU WILL DO
The first part of your journey at Boozt will be to take part in a thorough training program to create the best possible conditions for you to succeed and excel in your new role. Training sessions and development meetings will be held continuously throughout your time at Boozt.
Together with our trainers you will focus on your development and take part in training sessions to tailor your journey as a Boozter.
Provide top class service to our customers with all inquiries coming in via phone, email or chat

You speak and write fluently in Finnish.
You are also fluent in English since this is our corporate language and it is a part of your daily tasks to support other markets when needed
You enjoy solving problems, exceeding expectations and has a natural ability to connect with people
You see no obstacles in the challenges of offering quick, informative and individual answers and explanations even in stressful times
Previous experience in the service industry is a plus
Good communication skills and a real interest in expressing yourself well, both in speech and writing (tests will be given as part of our recruitment process)
You are proud of being precise and it is natural for you to be considerate in your behavior both internally and externally

OUR OFFER
This is a chance for you to join our vibrant Customer Service Team, an opportunity to grow and develop with one of the leading Nordic E-commerce companies
Full-time temporary employment for an initial 12 months with the possibility for a permanent position (the employment will start with a 6 month probation period)

BOOZT PERKS

A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility

We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?

We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.

Title: Data Scientist to Froda
Description:
About Froda
Froda was founded in 2015 with a clear vision – to revolutionize the banking experience for entrepreneurs by making it easy and affordable for them to invest in their ideas. Today, we are one of Sweden's fastest growing fintech with major international growth plans. We are a creative tech company with the ambition to turn a historically expensive and unfair industry into something ethical, sustainable, and forward thinking. Behind the company are several well-known investors and talents from e.g., Avanza, Spotify, Google, and Klarna.

About the Role
Froda is at the unique point of taking our data analytics and real-time decisioning to the next level. We are now looking for our next Data Scientist to help us transform our data into actionable insights.

You will design, develop, and maintain statistical data models in collaboration with our chief data scientist as well as our data engineers and analysts. Besides working with modeling you will also build and work on the data pipelines which feed our models. This is a key role in evolving Froda's data strategy as well as in the development and realization of our data platform.

Who are you?
We believe that you are a curious person who enjoys working in a team with other eager and open-minded people, who can’t wait to learn more and share their knowledge. You are driven by finding the right solution, in a business-oriented manner. We want you to be fluent in English and Swedish for this role, and to have a master's degree preferably in engineering, mathematics, or statistical modeling.
When it comes to your tech skills, we believe that you have experience of:
At least a couple of years as a Data Scientist or a similar role,
Working with statistical modeling in either Python, R, or similar,
Working extensively with SQL.
If you also have worked with machine learning, credit modeling, and maybe have programmed some in C#, Java, or similar, it is of course a plus!
So, what’s in it for you?
You will have the opportunity to work hands-on in a fast-paced, exciting, and collaborative scale-up company with ambitious co-workers that also honors the work-life balance. To add an edge to our employee offer we also have a warrant program for everybody working here.
At Froda, you will truly have freedom under responsibility, which means that you will have the ability to impact your own work and tackle a wider set of tasks than in a typical data science role. You have the actual possibilities to impact tech strategy and decisions. We are a passionate team with an open culture, and we truly believe that the best decisions are taken by combining people's knowledge!

If you have any questions or thoughts concerning the role or process, don’t hesitate to send me an email at: anna.sellhed@froda.se.

Title: Statistical Science Associate Director – Early Respiratory & Immunology Statistics, BioPharmaceuticals Biometrics
Description:
Are you passionate about statistics, confident to lead and collaborate with a curious mind? Are you keen to shape the future of statistics, transform the way we work with clinical trial design to build the basis for drug development? Then join the team unlocking the power of what science can do. Welcome to AstraZeneca!
At AstraZeneca, we put patients first and strive to meet their unmet needs worldwide, while applying groundbreaking approaches to science across many business areas. Working here means being entrepreneurial, thinking big and working together to make the impossible a reality. If you are swift to act, confident to lead, willing to collaborate, and curious about what science can do, then you’re our kind of person.
We are recruiting a Statistical Science Associate Director or Statistical Science Director to join our growing Early Respiratory & Immunology statistics team to support the Early Phase Respiratory & Immunology/Neurosciences/Vaccines & Infections portfolio. Our main focus is providing statistical project lead support for all of Early phase of clinical development for AZ’s Respiratory & Immunology, Neuroscience and Vaccines & Infections division together with specific targeted support for the development and innovation of Early Phase Biopharmaceutical trials.
In this role, you will belong to the Early Biometrics & Statistical Innovation (EB&SI) department, where our data-centric focus helps us work efficiently and creatively to bring the right medicines to the right patients. Our teams use their expertise in statistics and programming to address drug development objectives and reduce uncertainty in product development, driving better business decisions with quantitative reasoning. As part of the Data Science & AI team, you’ll use technology at the forefront of science in a creative environment, with the scope to develop new statistical ideas and apply them in your work.
Main duties and responsibilities
In this role you’ll lead the delivery and oversight on multiple studies/indications within multiple drug projects as a Global Project Statistician. You will work closely with the full team providing targeted statistical support to the Therapy Areas. You’ll participate in adapting and developing statistical methodology and participate in innovation workstreams facilitating innovation, improvement and development of how we do Early Phase Clinical trials.
With your unique skills you’ll contribute to the basis for innovative drug development. Working cross-functionally and within an international environment you’ll lead the statistical thinking and contribute to the delivery of early development studies, development plans, regulatory strategy, health technology assessment and commercial evaluation. As a subject matter expert and with excellent project management skills you’ll guide statistical staff and/or CRO partners, to ensure delivery to standards, quality and time. Additionally, you’ll mentor and support the education of early statistical talent.
Requirements
Essential
The minimum required education is a M.Sc./PhD degree in a relevant discipline such as statistics, biostatistics, or mathematical statistics
Experience in the relevant therapeutic areas
Strong knowledge of programming in R and/or SAS
Understanding of the technical and regulatory requirements related to the role
Excellent communication skills and desire to build strong collaborative relationships
Desire to apply your scientific competence on practical problems, for the benefit of patients
Desirable
Knowledge / research experience in the development of statistical methodology related to vaccines & infections, analysis and interpretation of safety data, observational studies, meta-analysis, Bayesian statistics, non-linear and mixed effect models.
Broad awareness of statistical issues against the evolving scientific and regulatory landscape

Title: AI developer
Description:
What is this about?
Synteda AB assist companies to embrace the era of artificial intelligence and Computer Vision effectively and take advantage of its vast possibilities by delivering innovative solutions. We understand how Computer Vision and AI can benefit the society. We stand ready to use our expertise to facilitate businesses in their journey into the era of AI. We work with several clients with various industry fields in close collaboration with top universities in Sweden.

Synteda is actively working on several unique products and solutions in various fields. Dream-innovate-create is our work process were our ideas go through different stages. We create successful solutions by checking feasibility of our product idea (POC) and develop our solution working with agile methodologies until we reach a complete full-scale product.

Synteda has a core team of highly qualified experts that provide assessment to identify challenges and explore different ideas to enhance effectiveness and develop specific algorithms to overcome company challenges. Synteda is built on ethical awareness, curiosity, transparency, respect, participation and last but not least science.

Synteda is growing rapidly and we are looking for a talented AI developer to join our team of experts.
What are we looking for?
Responsibilities
Work on our various platforms and customer assignments.
Design and implement algorithms for cutting edge products and platforms.
Develop advanced computer vision and AI techniques .
Design, implementation and optimization of AI algorithms.
Innovate and enforce IPR protection.
Validate, analyze and evaluate models.
Perform research, analysis and modeling on data.
Algorithm training, validation and testing.
Collaborate with cross-functional team members.

Required skills
Bachelor’s, Master’s, or Ph.D. degree in computer science or similar.
Programming experience in combination of Python, C#, C/C++, Spark, Java/Scala.
Knowledge of scientific computing language such as Matlab or R.
Strong knowledge in machine learning, deep learning, data science and computer vision.
Experience with analytics and image processing.
Experience with Neural networks and deep learning frameworks such as Torch, Tensorflow or PyTorch.
Experience with Python-based image and video manipulation frameworks (e.g. OpenCV, SciPy, Scikit-image, Pillow, Mahotas, Matplotlib, SimpleITK).
Good knowledge of cloud such as Google Cloud Platform, AWS and Azure.
Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.
Fluent in English, both spoken and written is required.
Advantage with Swedish.

BrightBid is a rapidly growing adtech company utilising AI and human expertise to create more refined Google Ads recommendations for businesses to drive customer acquisition. Title: Customer Service Agent
Description:
Customer Service Agent
THE OPPORTUNITY
Do you have an interest in fashion, see solutions rather than problems and always strive to provide service at a top level? Then this opportunity might be the one for you.
Do you also value a dynamic and international work environment, fun and knowledgeable colleagues as well as a lot of internal career opportunities, then apply and get the chance to join our amazing Customer Service Team.
As our new Customer Service Agent you will join a team, where you together will work towards providing world class service to our customers.
*
WHAT YOU WILL DO*
The first part of your journey at Boozt will be to take part in a thorough training program to create the best possible conditions for you to succeed and excel in your new role. Training sessions and development meetings will be held continuously throughout your time at Boozt.
Together with our trainers you will focus on your development and take part in training sessions to tailor your journey as a Boozter.
Provide top class service to our customers with all inquiries coming in via phone, email or chat
Be our expert when it comes to questions ranging from specific product information, to styling tips, stock status, shipping details, payment queries, and campaign errands
You will be the company’s eyes and ears and will be a truly important part of the “from order to delivery chain” to ensure that we reach our goal of building an unrivaled customer experience
*
YOUR PROFILE*
You speak and write fluently in one of the following languages Swedish, Norwegian or Finnish
You are also fluent in English since this is our corporate language and it is a part of your daily tasks to support other markets when needed
You enjoy solving problems, exceeding expectations and has a natural ability to connect with people
You see no obstacles in the challenges of offering quick, informative and individual answers and explanations even in stressful times
Previous experience in the service industry is a plus
Good communication skills and a real interest in expressing yourself well, both in speech and writing (tests will be given as part of our recruitment process)
You are proud of being precise and it is natural for you to be considerate in your behavior both internally and externally
*
OUR OFFER*
This is a chance for you to join our vibrant Customer Service Team, an opportunity to grow and develop with one of the leading Nordic E-commerce companies
Full-time temporary employment for an initial 12 months with the possibility for a permanent position (the employment will start with a 6 month probation period)
Working hours for the Swedish and Danish teams are 8:00-17:00, 10:00-19:00 and 13:00-22:00 on a rolling schedule.
Working hours for the Norwegian and Finnish teams are 8:00-17:00 and 10:00-19:00 on a rolling schedule.
Your working schedule will be published for you to see four months in advance
You will join a big international team where we support and learn from each other, but the most important of all we have fun while doing so
Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.
_
We look forward to your application!_
*
BOOZT PERKS*
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor
*
A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US*
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.
Job Types: Full-time, Contract

Title: Computer vision engineers
Description:
Blue Cromos
Are you looking for a new adventure with a modern IT startup? Look no further, at Blue Cromos we offer a chance to work in a fast-growing tech environment based in Malmö. We are a company that is branching out with exciting new solutions helping companies like automotive, pharma, industrial and luxury goods hindering the tragedy that is counterfeits. We believe it is our duty to develop tomorrow's sustainable global manufacturing.

Required skills
Master degree or equivalent level in Machine Learning, Computer Vision, Data Science or associated areas.
Self-driven problem solver with a strong sense of teamwork.
Strong theoretical knowledge in Computer Vision, Machine Learning, Image Analysis, Mathematics, Physics.
Good coding skills and knowledge of C++/Python.
Previous experience of using frameworks such as TensorFlow/Keras, OpenCV, data manipulation and visualization frameworks.

Strong Advantages

Prior software development experience.
Familiar with agile software development.
Publications in the machine learning/computer vision sector.

Skills in:
Object detection.
Image processing.
Image classification.
Mathematics and Physics.
Deep Learning and Computer Vision concepts.
Software Development.

Why work at Blue Cromos?
Blue Cromos offers you a chance to work in a fast-growing Tech environment.
We place a great deal of thought on making sure that our employees are offered a modern and stimulating work environment where everyone fits in.
At our company you´ll be a part of a highly ambitious and supportive team that keeps growing. We think it´s important to work hard and aim high whiles having a great time with you colleagues. Everyone on the team is equally skilled at working alone and in a collaborative environment. Afterworks

Competitive salary, pension, and insurance

Additional information
