Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Electrolux Professional presents:

DATA ENGINEER
Ljungby, Sweden

As part of the Electrolux Professional team, one day is never the same as the next. But what drives us every day is our mission to make our customers’ work-life easier, more profitable – and truly sustainable. Becoming their OnE trusted partner, managing their complete operations. Understanding their daily journey – and making it a winning one - whether they run a hotel, restaurant, laundry or café. Acting truly sustainable means going beyond products; connecting users with intelligence, humans with technology and innovative thinkers with relevant business models. And providing the most inclusive service offering with expertise, state-of-the-art interfaces and the best people network. Together with you, we will grow and create sustainable experiences for people and the world around us, in food, beverage and laundry.

A REGULAR DAY AT WORK
In this role you will evaluate and develop new technology solutions for our professional laundry, food and beverage appliances. You work in the Advanced Development (AD) team located in Ljungby, Sweden, in close collaboration also with colleagues of the AD team in Vallenoncello, Italy. Cross-functional collaboration is a vital part of your work, in particular with Product Managers, the Design, the Electronics, the Product Development and the Lab teams, as well as Purchasing and Production. Your work environment is truly international, serving all five Business Areas (see About Electrolux Professional, below) with R&D teams and production sites on three continents. Therefore digital work tools and remote collaboration is a natural part of your work and some business travels occur. But you will also spend a lot of time in the physical world, doing experiments and testing prototypes in our modern and spacious lab in Ljungby.

YOUR MAIN RESPONSIBILITIES
Lead the activities related to data analysis and machine learning within an AD project.
Create models based on noisy and non-linear data (understand and formalize problem, create dataset, create and train models,…).
Implement the integration of models into a product together with control system specialists.
Proactively align objectives, tasks and technical aspects with your colleagues.

YOU
Are Customer Obsessed - You actively listen to understand our internal and external customers’ needs and deliver value.
Build Trust - You are accountable, share information and take ownership of your area of specialty.
Are Bold - You can work independently without detailed directions. You get things done. You are not afraid of making mistakes and you learn from them.
Act sustainably - You always act in an ethical and responsible way, and you have sustainability in mind in whatever you do. You build for the future.
You are curious about people and about stuff. You want to learn, to improve and to build something bigger together with others.

EDUCATION & EXPERIENCE
Degree (master or higher) in data science / computer science / mathematics / software or other engineering.
Specialization and practical experience in machine learning and other data analysis methods.
At least 2 years of practical experience, more desired.
Good general programming skills
Experience with Raspberry Pi is a plus
Good proficiency in written and spoken English. Swedish communication is a plus.

Please apply by: 31.12.2022

About Electrolux Professional
Electrolux Professional is one of the leading global providers of food service, beverage and laundry for professional users. Our innovative products and worldwide service network make our customers’ work-life easier, more profitable – and truly sustainable every day. Our solutions and products are manufactured in 13 plants in seven countries and sold in over 110 countries. In 2021, Electrolux Professional had global sales of SEK 7,9bn and approximately 4,000 employees. Electrolux Professional’s B-shares are listed at Nasdaq Stockholm. From July 1, our global business is divided into five Business Areas (BA): BA Beverage & Food Preparation, BA Laundry, BA Food Americas, BA Food APAC & MEA and BA Food Europe.
For more information, visit https://www.electroluxprofessional.com

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
This is Readly
Readly is a digital subscription service where users across 50 markets have unlimited, “all-you-can-read” access to 7,500 national and international magazines and newspapers - all in one app. Readly has partnered with 1,200+ publishers around the globe to drive the digital transformation in our industry and contribute to thriving societies and a healthy planet.
Our passionate team of 150+ people in Sweden, Germany, France and the UK, have created a value-driven ecosystem where all our stakeholders share the purpose of bringing inspiration and insight into people’s daily lives and unlocking meaningful moments of relaxation.
Since September 2020 Readly is listed at Nasdaq Stockholm.

About the role
We are looking for more data-focused engineers to support our journey towards building more personalized and data-driven products. We currently have two teams who work on ingesting, curating, and preparing data for analytical and operational use. The teams are expected to take ownership of the over full lifecycle of data and support existing data products like recommendation- and search engines. Which team you fit in will depend on your profile and interests. Our cross-functional teams, consisting of data scientists, data engineers and software developers, also work closely with the Analytics- and CRM-teams to create a personal Readly experience in all touchpoints with our users.
At the company we work with the following technologies:
AWS as our cloud service provider
Snowflake (and Redshift) as a data warehouse solution
dbt for data transformation and dependency management
Ruby/Go/Python as mainly used programming languages
Terraform as IaC tool
Step functions for data job orchestration
Gitlab for code versioning and deployment pipelines


What is expected from you
It is expected of you to have a great understanding of the data engineering area as well as basic understanding of the data science area. While it’s not important which service provider, experience working with modern Data Engineering in a cloud environment is essential for the job. Having hands-on experience working with the exact technologies we use is not a requirement although working with similar products within the same area is a must. We have, however, made a bet on Snowflake as our primary data warehouse, so Snowflake experience is a big plus. As we are building a lot of new and exciting services and products, your input on a lot of critical and long-lasting decisions will be greatly appreciated. Therefore, it is important that you have a good level of knowledge about what it means to develop a data product, from data modelling to robust deployment strategies for data pipelines. Good communication skills and ability to work in a team with a culture of knowledge sharing is of course a must as well.

Application
Do you feel this is a perfect match? Please apply by clicking the link below!

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Want to work with the latest technologies such as AWS, Snowflake and Tableau? Are you curious as a person and want to join a change journey from report driven ways of working to create a self-service tool?

You will belong to one of our analytics team with people that are working close together, which also creates a great team spirit in moving towards the same direction, making TUI more data-driven with more insights.

Do you want to work in an environment where travel is the core business? Do you enjoy travelling yourself? That’s great, keep on reading!

To be truly data-driven we are looking for great people who want to make a change. In TUI’s insights change journey you will learn a lot, get challenged and deliver great insights for the stakeholders, which in turn will affect how they make business decisions.

ABOUT THE JOB
You will manage the pipelining (collection, storage, access), engineering (cleansing, feature creation / selection) and understanding (documentation, exploration) of the data
Acquire, create and manage innovative data assets for the team. These assets will draw from various sources – internal and external systems, flat files, databases and external APIs
Evaluate user requests for new or re-engineered analytics and reporting solutions to determine their feasibility, time requirements and their compatibility with current systems and architecture standards
Active participation in the development of the data lake, data marts and subsequent enhancements, including the creation of new data solutions to support development of analytic capabilities
Interact with stakeholders regarding data availability and report format/presentation, to ensure the report provides the information the stakeholders need without compromising the report’s accuracy
ABOUT YOU

The ability to design, implement and use effective database structures to ensure data is organised effectively and ready for downstream development of data science and analytics
Experience of Big Data platforms, enabling non-technical users to gain insights into key business metrics

Solid understanding of data warehousing principles, concepts and best practices
Hands on experience with modern data storage systems (e.g. S3)
Feeling comfortable using Cloud Analytics Technologies, preferably AWS
Some experience with contarnization such as Kubernetes or Docker
Strong SQL and data profiling skills; hands-on ETL experience (e.g. DBT)
Familiarity with a traditional BI application such as Tableau, Power BI, or Spotfire
We see that you are: collaborative, innovative and structured. Collaboration because you will belong to a team. Innovative and structured since you will be a part of an insights change journey’
An education in software engineering, informatics, vocational education in analytics or similar is preferred
Our business language is English, so you need to be proficient in the language
You will work for TUI Nordics so it would be great if you are proficient in either Swedish, Norwegian or Danish

ABOUT OUR OFFER
Great location and open space offices
Excellent career development opportunities
Fantastic holiday benefits including discounts
Online wellbeing and learning support
Fun and dynamic work culture
Hybrid work – we offer flexible work model where TUI employees work at least half of the time in the office


We love to see your uniqueness shine through and inspire the future of travel. If you would like to read more about what Diversity & Inclusion means to us simply visit Our DNA.
We are looking forward to your application and meeting you!

Do you have questions about the recruitment process, contact Farid Dadsetan at farid.dadsetan@tui.se.

In this recruitment we are primarly hiring people with permanent residency (PR) in Sweden. We do not support relocations or work visas.

Title: Junior Product Manager - Acquisition
Description:
Join us in changing how pet care is provided worldwide!
FirstVet is the first truly digital veterinary clinic. We let pet owners meet with licensed veterinarians via their mobile or computer. Our solution contributes to a more balanced and better functioning care process for all parties. By providing a first point of contact for all pet owners FirstVet makes pet care more available, more efficient, and more qualitative.
The role
We are looking for a Junior product manager with solid knowledge of marketing strategy to join our Acquisition team. You will work in the team responsible for our website, firstvet.com, which includes everything that happens to our customers outside of our virtual clinic. As part of this, you will work side by side with marketing to accelerate our acquisition of customers and retention of customers across all verticals. This includes SEO, SEM, tracking, content, retention and cross-sell.
We are a remote-first team with a headquarters in Stockholm. You will work with your international team to drive our worldwide product vision and product. You will have a lot of international contacts with our different country organizations to best ensure continuous growth in all our markets.

The opportunity for you:
The sky is the limit - At this fast-growing scale-up (doubling our tech and product department in the past year) there is a lot of room to grow. You will work with your product manager counterparts to build a personal development plan to become (even) better at your craft.
Solve real problems - FirstVet is focused on ensuring we do the right things for pet parents which results in great medical outcomes and fulfilling lives for their pets. You will have a direct impact on us achieving this and hopefully your passion for pets will shine through!
Build the growth levers that will accelerate and deepen our relationship with customers. You will build the product growth strategy that helps customers understand our value proposition and stay engaged with our ecosystem of services


Your responsibilities:

Own the product vision, strategy, and roadmap for acquisition of new pet parents globally across Web, iOS, and Android.
Understand and improve the effectiveness of the different channels available to us, including SEO, SEM, CRM, messaging, and other campaigns.
Work with our data science and user research teams to identify key growth opportunities, and translate those insights into hypotheses, tests, and features that can improve the product.
Represent and support our marketing team to ensure we are able to bring our brand into our product, and that our customers understand the value we offer.
Build strong, collaborative relationships across design, engineering, and marketing to help coordinate efforts and drive adoption and usage.
Work with the wider Product and Tech leadership team to shape overall product strategy


The person we are looking for has:
1+ years as a product manager in a high performing, growth oriented, and cross-functional team in an agile environment, preferably towards B2C
Are analytically skilled, data driven, and feel comfortable to track and manage KPIs, enjoy working with large amounts of data and have a demonstrated ability to understand key performance drivers and ability to execute against findings
A customer-centric approach with a good understanding of UX design principles and familiarity using research, analytics and experimentation to guide decision making
Experience conducting A/B testing and funnel optimization techniques
It is considered a plus if you have previous experience working on growth, onboarding or acquisition
Full professional proficiency in English with excellent written and verbal communication skills


Apart from the above-mentioned requirements, it goes without saying that an interest in animals is highly desirable. We’re a pet-oriented organization and it’s not unusual to run into our office dogs or for a cat to join our video calls!

Title: Data Scientist - Acceleration Nordics
Description:
Välkommen att ansluta till ett erfaret och växande team med data scientists och konsulter som jobbar med att driva ökad effekt av marknadsföringen för några av Sveriges och världens största varumärken.
Som en del av den ledande mediebyråkoncernen GroupM arbetar vi på Acceleration med att omvandla stora datamängder till lösningar på komplexa problemställningar inom media och marknadsföring. Projekten inkluderar såväl machine learning, konsulttjänster och strategiprojekt som algoritmer och dashboards.
Acceleration driver GroupM och resten av industrin framåt genom innovation kring teknik och data och jobbar nära de största annonsörerna, publicisterna och teknikbolagen inom industrin. Detta är en position med en uppsjö av möjligheter till tillväxt både professionellt och personligt.
Om tjänsten
Tjänsten innefattar att i ett team med erfarna kollegor:
Vara drivande data scientist i projekt inom ekonometri, attribution, lyftstudier, experiment, algoritmer och andra data science-relaterade projekt
Tillsammans med övriga projektteamet analysera, paketera och presentera mot våra kunder
Vara med och driva utvecklingsprojekt inom automatiserad rapportering, algoritmer samt övriga data science-åtaganden

Professionella och personliga kvalifikationer
Vi är ett team präglat av hög nivå som tror på ständig utveckling och en entreprenöriell drivkraft.
Professionellt tror vi att du är nyutexaminerad alternativt arbetat ett antal år inom data science eller analys med följande kunskaper:
Utbildning med en solid grund i matematik och statistik (t.ex. civilingenjör inom matematik, industriell ekonomi, alternativt ekonom eller statistiker med kvantitativt fokus)
Under studietiden berört statistiska metoder och modeller, inklusive regressionsanalys och variansanalys
Stark kunskap inom Microsoft Office-sviten - PowerPoint och framför allt Excel
Förmåga att presentera och kommunicera dina resultat på ett övertygande sätt
Kunskap om olika statistiska verktyg i R och Python samt analysverktyg som PowerBI och tillämpningar inom Cloud-miljöer är en fördel (men inte ett krav)
Kunskap inom ekosystemet för digital media och miljöer inom exempelvis Google Marketing Platform, Facebook och Xandr är en fördel (men inte krav)
Kunskap inom marskininlärning och AI är en fördel (men inte krav)
På ett personligt plan tror vi att du är intresserad av att:
Presentera och kommunicera dina resultat till relevanta stakeholders
Driva dialoger och leverera projekt på såväl svenska som engelska
Arbeta grundligt, detaljorienterat och självständigt (proaktivt och entreprenöriellt)
Vara en ”lagspelare” med vilja att arbeta både individuellt och i team

Vi erbjuder dig
Hos oss får du möjligheten att arbeta med många av Sveriges och världens mest ambitiösa varumärken, tillsammans med ett team som brinner för digital marknadsföring, och med marknadsledande teknologier. Du kommer att sitta i centrala lokaler på Birger Jarlsgatan med inspirerande kollegor från olika bakgrunder, som tillsammans driver digital marknadsföring till nästa nivå genom innovation och gediget arbete. Vidare finns stora möjligheter för personlig utveckling och karriärsutveckling inom GroupM Sverige, såväl som inom vårt globala nätverk.
Övrigt
Vi är ett familjärt företag som är en del av WPP, en stor internationell koncern, och vi arbetar för att kombinera det bästa av dessa två världar. Du erbjuds att arbeta på en stimulerande och utvecklande arbetsplats med hög trivselfaktor och kollegor som har nära till skratt.
Förutom det självklara, som bra arbetsvillkor, trevlig arbetsmiljö och spännande utmaningar så finns det ett par saker som gör det lite extra bra att jobba här:
Stor delaktighet och möjlighet att vara med och påverka ditt dagliga arbete
Familjär anda, korta beslutsvägar och stor närhet mellan ledning och medarbetare
Vi tycker att balans mellan arbete, fritid och personlig utveckling är viktigt
Friskvårdsbidrag på 3000 kr/år och flertal attraktiva personalförmåner
Vi erbjuder marknadsanpassade pensionsvillkor och privatrådgivning av pension via vår samarbetspartner Söderberg & Partners
Vi har företagshälsovård via Feelgood och en extra hälsoförsäkring via Skandia
Konferenser, kick-offs och annat kul som vi gör gemensamt
Kontor centralt beläget mitt i stan på Birger Jarlsgatan
Ansökan & tjänst
Tjänsten är en tillsvidareanställning på heltid med tillträde efter sommaren. Vi tillämpar sex månaders provanställning.
Urval och intervjuer sker löpande, så skicka så snart som möjligt in din ansökan med CV och personligt brev.
Kontakt
Har du frågor kring tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta Andreas Nordfors (andreas.nordfors@acceleration.biz)Director Sweden, Acceleration. Vi tar inte emot ansökningar via epost.


Om GroupM

GroupM är en av Sveriges största mediebyrågrupper och består av Wavemaker, MediaCom, Mindshare och Acceleration. GroupM:s främsta mål är att skapa fördelar för våra kunder via samarbeten med gruppens byråer. Det gör vi bland annat genom skalfördelar inom trading, teknik och data. Vi är en del av WPP som är en av världens största koncerner inom marknadskommunikation med över 190 000 medarbetare på global basis. GroupM Sverige har cirka 350 medarbetare i Stockholm, Göteborg och Malmö.

Title: Utvecklare - Machine Learning
Description:
Calvia levererar spetskompetens inom AI och Machine Learning. Vi predikterar och automatiserar central information för våra kunder som effektiviserar och gör dem mer lönsamma.

Vi söker nu en passionerad, driven och lösningsorienterad medarbetare till vårt AI/ML och Advanced Analytics team för att vidareutveckla vår Machine Learning plattform och tillämpade lösningar.

Kompetens:
Full Python data science stack
Pandas
Scikit-learn (Sklearn)
Seaborn

Erfarenhet av utveckling i Cloud med DevOps, kontinuerlig integrering och tillämpning i Azure eller AWS. Alternativt, python backend utveckling med ramverk som Flask / Tornado / Pyramid / Django.

Bekant med maskininlärning-algoritmer som Random forest och Gradient boosting.

Kommunicera obehindrat på svenska och engelska.

Dina mjuka färdigheter är passion och uthållighet för långsiktiga mål. Öppen, ödmjuk och flexibel samt hungrig efter ny kunskap.

Calvia erbjuder början på en karriär inom AI/ML och Avancerad analys eller nå högre höjder inom morgondagens AI/ML.

Förutom att du har stor frihet att påverka ditt arbete, stimulerar och vägleder Calvia din karriär inom området Advanced Analytics och AI/ML.

Du som person
Du är öppen och kommunikativ i ditt arbete och ser alltid nya möjligheter. Du är en problemlösare som drivs av engagemang, noggrannhet och struktur. Självständighet och integritet samt viljan att dela dina kunskaper till medarbetare är självklarheter som tilltalar dig.

Vi på Calvia
Calvia erbjuder dig ett utmanande arbete där du har möjlighet att utvecklas. Hos Calvia kommer du få möjlighet att arbeta i projekt med tekniskt ansvar för moderna lösningar. Du kommer att arbeta i ett företag där egna initiativ, samarbete och engagemang värdesätts och premieras samtidigt som du utvecklas. Calvias kultur styrs av värdeskapande, laganda och passion för verksamhetsutveckling.

Stämmer detta in på dig? Då vill vi träffa dig
Kontakta gärna Harald Rohlin
E-post job@calvia.se Tel +46 736009300

Title: Trainee - Verksamhetsutvecklare digitalisering av transportsystemet
Description:
Om jobbet
Under tolv månader deltar du i ett omfattande traineeprogram som främjar din personliga utveckling, breddar ditt kontaktnät och ger dig kunskap om våra olika verksamheter. Du rustas i förändrings- och projektledning och tillsammans med övriga traineer deltar du i utvecklingsuppdrag utifrån olika case för att lära och påverka. Du förväntas att själv ta initiativ, etablera kontakter och planera en stor del av ditt traineeår. Som exempel kan du välja att göra studiebesök eller kortare praktikperioder inom de verksamheter som intresserar dig. Det erbjuds möjlighet till samverkan med andra myndigheter och externa aktörer i Sverige och internationellt. I arbetet ingår resor, både nationellt och regionalt.
Vi på avdelning Transportkvalitet ser fram emot att välkomna dig som trainee! Vår avdelning ansvarar för expertstöd och analyser inom tillgänglighet för personer och gods, trafiksäkerhet, miljö, hälsa samt klimat. Huvuduppdraget är att fånga in omvärldens krav och behov samt samverka med samhällets aktörer för att bidra till att de transportpolitiska målen nås. Vårt motto är att vara en expertavdelning i världsklass där vår kunskap gör skillnad. Vår avdelning tar, genom forskning tillsammans med andra aktörer, fram ny kunskap. Vi har omfattande samarbete på EU-nivå och stöttar regeringen inom avdelningens kompetensområden. Som trainee är du med i hela avdelningens verksamhet och du kommer bland annat att:
genomföra analyser och utredningar, bedriva omvärldsbevakning, benchmarking och föreslå utvecklingsinsatser
delta i verksamhetsområdets datadrivna analyslab där vi genomför avancerade analyser inom avdelningens expertområden
stödja verksamheten i projekt- och förändringsledning när nya initiativ ska implementeras, detta görs genom insatser för att utveckla den digitala transportinfrastrukturen
medverka i utvecklingsarbete av analytiska metoder, verktyg och tillgång till data samt kommunicera val av metod och resultat
delta i EU-arbete i projekt samt vara expertstöd inom digitaliseringsområdet
Jag som blir din chef heter Petter Åsman. Jag är chef för Enheten Gods & ITS, en av avdelningen Transportkvalitets åtta enheter. Vi är en nationell expertenhet inom gods och logistik samt intelligenta transportsystem (ITS). På enheten är vi idag 14 medarbetare som stöttar Trafikverket med expertstöd inom våra områden. Såhär beskriver en av våra medarbetare som tidigare varit trainee den traineeåret:
"Det är ett roligt, utvecklande jobb, med många nya utmaningar. Som trainee får du en unik möjlighet att jobba över verksamhetsområdena och få en insikt i hela Trafikverkets verksamhet, vilket är till stor nytta efter traineetiden", säger Jonna som började som trainee på enheten och idag arbetar som utredare med inriktning ITS och digitalisering.
Kvalifikationer
För att trivas som trainee behöver du ha ett stort intresse för att utveckla transportsystemet kombinerat med ett digitaliseringsintresse och förståelse för digital omställning samt en vilja att medverka till att skapa innovation. Arbetet innebär många kontakter både inom och utanför Trafikverket och förutsätter att du som person är duktig på att skapa goda relationer, kommunicera och förmedla budskap på ett enkelt sätt anpassat till mottagaren. Du drivs av att arbeta i en föränderlig miljö och jobbar självständigt, ser vad som behöver göras och agerar därefter. Du har en stark egen drivkraft och besitter en mycket god problemlösningsförmåga som gör att du identifierar problem och utvecklar lösningar ur ett helhetsperspektiv.
Vi söker dig som
har civilingenjörs- eller masterexamen inom samhällsbyggnad, transport, fordon, information eller industriell ekonomi
har mycket goda kunskaper i svenska i tal och skrift
Det är meriterande med kurser eller examensarbete inom Data Science/AI, Big data analytics, visualisering av data, business intelligence, statistik i dataanalys eller innovation/innovationsledning.
Din akademiska examen ska ha uttagits under 2021, 2022, alternativt kommer du att ta din examen senast september 2023.
Övrig information
Vi använder främst mail (från mejladress: noreply@heroma.se) för att göra utskick och kallelser. Kolla din inkorg och även skräppost/SPAM regelbundet under denna tid för att vara säker på att du får all information från oss! I denna rekrytering används webbaserade tester som en del i urvalet.
När du ansöker ska du inte bifoga något personligt brev. Istället för att bifoga personligt brev, får du möjlighet i ansökningsformuläret att beskriva varför du är intresserad av den här tjänsten. Detta är en tillsvidaretjänst som inleds med en provanställning på 6 månader. Tillträde till tjänsten är den 1 september 2023.
De första intervjuerna är planerade att hållas den 6-9 mars 2023 via Skype.
#LI-AB2
Ansökan
De frågor som du får besvara när du skickar in din ansökan kommer att ligga till grund för det första urvalet vi gör.
Som sökande till Trafikverket kan du eventuellt behöva gå igenom en säkerhetsprövning. Den innehåller säkerhetsprövningssamtal och registerkontroll innan anställning, om tjänsten är placerad i säkerhetsklass. I vissa fall krävs svenskt medborgarskap för säkerhetsklassade tjänster.
På Planering skapar vi innovativa lösningar som bidrar till att nå de transportpolitiska målen, såsom klimatmålen och nollvisionen. Vi planerar Sveriges statliga infrastruktur för väg och järnväg samt långsiktigt även för sjö- och luftfart. Hos oss arbetar du nära den politiska arenan och våra samarbetspartners - men framförallt nära medborgare och näringsliv.
På Trafikverket jobbar vi med att göra Sverige närmare. Vi tror på att en förening av olika erfarenheter, bakgrunder och perspektiv är den bästa grunden för att bygga en arbetsplats fri från diskriminering och en miljö där alla trivs och gör sitt bästa. Vi tror på mångfald där den gemensamma nämnaren är pålitlighet, engagemang och mod. För det är så vi bäst representerar vårt samhälle.

Title: Regulatory and Start Up Specialist (RSUS)(FSP)
Description:
Job Overview
Perform tasks at a country level associated with Site Activation (SA) activities in accordance with applicable local and/or international regulations, standard operating procedures (SOPs), project requirements and contractual/budgetary guidelines. May also include maintenance activities.
Essential Functions
Under general supervision, serve as Single Point of Contact (SPOC) in assigned studies for investigative sites, Site Activation Manager (SAM), Project Management team, and other departments as necessary.
Ensure adherence to standard operating procedures (SOPs), Work Instructions (WIs), quality of designated deliverables and project timelines.
Perform start up and site activation activities according to applicable regulations, SOPs and work instructions.
Distribute completed documents to sites and internal project team members.
Prepare site regulatory documents, reviewing for completeness and accuracy.
Ensure accurate completion and maintenance of internal systems, databases and tracking tools with project specific information.
Review and provide feedback to management on site performance metrics.
Review, establish and agree on project planning and project timelines.
Ensure monitoring measures are in place and implement contingency plan as needed.
Inform team members of completion of regulatory and contractual documents for individual sites.
Review, track and follow up the progress, the approval and execution of documents, regulatory, ethics, Informed Consent Form (ICF), and Investigator Pack (IP) release documents, in line with project timelines.
Provide local expertise to SAMs and project team during initial and on-going project timeline planning.
Perform quality control of documents provided by sites.
May have direct contact with sponsors on specific initiatives.
Qualifications
Bachelor's Degree Bachelor’s Degree in life sciences or a related field and 3 years’ clinical research or other relevant experience; or equivalent combination of education, training and experience.
3 years clinical research experience, including 1 year experience in a leadership capacity. Equivalent combination of education, training and experience.
In-depth knowledge of clinical systems, procedures, and corporate standards.
Good negotiating and communication skills with ability to challenge, if applicable.
Effective communication, organizational, and interpersonal skills. Swedish Language Skills is a MUST
Ability to work independently and to effectively prioritize tasks.
Ability to manage multiple projects.
Knowledge and ability to apply GCP/ICH and applicable regulatory guidelines.
Knowledge of applicable regulatory requirements, including local regulations, , SOPs and company’s Corporate Standards.
Understanding of regulated clinical trial environment and knowledge of drug development process.
Ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with coworkers, managers and clients.
IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions and clinical research services to the life sciences industry. We believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com

Title: Venture Lead, Tech and Product
Description:
Company
Culture: Startup
Size: Medium
Swedish: English OK
Role
Leadership: Self
Experience: Young Talent
Stack: Cutting Edge
EQT Ventures is a multi-stage, multi-sector fund whose mission is to support ambitious founders on their journeys to global success. Founded six years ago here in Stockholm, we’ve spread out to offices in San Francisco, London, Paris, Amsterdam, and Berlin. In addition to our investment team, who are former founders and operators, we have a deep bench of operational talent in marketing, engineering, design, data science, finance, and scaling to support entrepreneurs. At the same time, we’re disrupting the very industry we work in: we’ve built an internal machine learning platform called Motherbrain to scout the world for great startups before anyone knows about them.
About the role
We’re looking to bring on a Venture Lead who loves tech and product to our Stockholm office, since our last one got promoted recently. You’ll work in our investment team on deal work, sourcing, and evaluating new opportunities across the Nordic region.
Meet and evaluate early-stage and scale-up companies. Move from a high level-analysis phase to a deeper understanding of what the opportunities ahead are, and how a specific company can help be a part of the solution.
Create lasting relationships with Founders, regardless if EQT Ventures in the end invests or not. We strongly believe that informal and transparent feedback to Founders is the best way to help long term.
Understand what kind of teams, products, companies have the potential to solve important problems, and hence be interesting and attractive investment opportunities for EQT Ventures.
Collaborate with the rest of the EQT Ventures team in putting together the best internal team to help and assess the Founders we meet. You are humble and understand that we are generalists with an information disadvantage, but that we use our team’s strength to make high-quality decisions.
Drive the investment process forward independently, and enjoy the mix of working alone and with colleagues. The process can be ambiguous at times and is always evolving.
A successful Venture Lead meets a ton of people every year, loves discussing problems, ideas, and the future, and has a great sense for which founders/companies to spend more time with to assess if we are a good match. The Venture Lead eventually fights for these founders internally at EQT Ventures as we discuss potential investments in the greater team, and combines passion with analytical insight to build a case of why the fund should invest.
About you
The ideal candidate is a curious, fast learner who has been a part of a tech startup journey already, but now wants to try out what it’s like to invest in companies rather than running them yourself. No education requirement (some of our partners are self-taught and university dropouts), but we believe you are a people’s person who loves tech and crazy ideas and has a high-risk appetite since odds are almost never in a venture capitalist’s favor.
To make our team even stronger and more diverse, we are looking for someone with experience in product development and / or technical experience. Preferably operationally in a startup, scaleup, or larger venture-funded tech company.
More about EQT Ventures
We are one of the largest VC firms in Europe with €1.2bn AUM, we have made investments into over 100 companies — adding 28 new ones to our portfolio in 2021 alone. We are immensely proud of the companies we work with including Wolt, Einride, Handshake, Moralis, Luko, and Cleo to name a few. EQT’s core values are entrepreneurial, transparent, informal, collaborative, and respectful. We have a high moral compass and want to do good in the world.

Title: AI/ML Applied Research Scientist
Description:
Does helping to make life better for millions of people by improving healthcare outcomes around the world motivate you? If the answer is yes, you think just like us. We, Mölnlycke, are a world-leading medical solutions company, designing and supplying medical solutions to enhance performance in healthcare – from the hospital to the home.
Continuing to invest in our future, we are looking for a collaborative, creative, and detail-oriented AI/ML Engineer (Data Scientist) who can come on-board and apply deep knowledge of AI/ML to bring Mölnlycke to the forefront of the data-informed decision-making culture.

Our ideal candidate has worked in a data scientist or an AI/ML engineer role wherein he/she is comfortable working with unknowns, evaluating the data and the feasibility of applying appropriate AI/ML techniques to business problems and has a track record of developing and deploying AI/ML models into live applications.

You are comfortable handling big data (both structured and unstructured), with a strong maths, stats, data science and programming background, as well as strong engineering know-how to operationalise AI/ML solutions in the production environment.

This role is available in either Sweden or UK but a strong candidate from other major European countries, e.g. Germany, Italy, Belgium will be considered.

Key Accountabilities:
Apply deep technical expertise in solving various real-world business problems, whether it be commercial, operational, or clinical, through the application of AI and Machine Learning
Collaborate with other team members both within and outside the Applied Data Science team to create and deliver world-class data science solutions
Apply advanced machine learning techniques to build prototypes with various AI-related libraries and write production-ready code in Python, according to best coding and object-oriented programming practices
Contribute to developing a business case through a detailed business analysis and process mapping to identify key decision points to address and suggest continuous improvement within the area
Get involved in defining the scope of data science projects and the AI roadmap, working collaboratively with the business stakeholders and other partners, e.g. IT, Legal, Finance, and People
Develop clear, concise communication to explain relevant Machine Learning, data science concepts and model outputs to the business stakeholders
Visualise and translate model outputs into easily understandable, actionable insights for the stakeholders
Research and develop new techniques while helping define an AI ecosystem covering data infrastructure, frameworks, open source tools, data science languages, etc.
Stay up to date with the latest development in Data Science and AI by attending conferences and lead thought leadership by publishing papers

Key Decisions:
Selection of models and technical approach to solve a business problem
Choice of data science tools, frameworks, and data infrastructure to define and build an AI ecosystem, working with IT
AI strategy and roadmap aligned with the business strategies, working with senior leadership and relevant stakeholders
Training requirements and hiring

Capabilities, Experience & Qualifications:
Essential:
PhD or master’s degree in a STEM field involving machine learning, computer science, and statistics
5-10 years' professional experience in data science
A track record of successfully building and productising AI solutions using various ML techniques
Research and innovation skills with the ability to understand and explain to others, publications on advanced machine learning and computer science as well as the ability to prototype, evaluate and adapt / improve the ideas discussed in the publications
Hands-on experience in frameworks like SciKit-Learn and TensorFlow / PyTorch
Good grasp of classical statistical methods, e.g. fitting regression models, inference testing and sampling
Excellent programming skills in Python (Object-Oriented Programming), with a good understanding of coding practices and version control software such as Git
Practical cross-functional experience in R&D, marketing, sales, finance, and operations (ideally in the life science industry)
Data wrangling with tools like Hive and Spark and libraries like Pandas, NumPy and SciPy
Hands-on experience in using various techniques to handle data issues, e.g. a lack of data, missing data, imbalanced data, incorrect data, outliers, etc.
Experience with Rest APIs and CLIs
Excellent communication and teamwork
High proficiency in English

Desirable:
Experience in any of the following:
NLP / NLU / NLI – topic modelling, word embeddings, semantic ontology, etc.
OCR – document processing and data extraction
Computer vision and image processing
Experience in setting up an AI ecosystem to enable building, training and deployment of AI/ML models
Experience in ML Life Cycle Management, i.e. containerization (Docker, Kubernetes), APIfication, MLOps, etc.
Familiar with client-server and microservice architecture
Experience of working in cloud environments, e.g. Azure, Snowflake
MedTech / Life Science domain experience
Agile development skills and experience

Title: Databricks Data Engineer - Malmö
Description:
Interested in belonging to the strongest Databricks community in the Nordics? Learning from experienced architects and getting access to lots of upskilling material and courses? Then we’re looking for you.
What You’ll Do
In your role as a Databricks Data Engineer you will be working with the latest tools within data ingestion, ETL and reliable orchestration for data, analytics & AI. We work with both batch and streaming data that powers analytics dashboards & productionized machine learning models.
As a Global Strategic Partner with Databricks, our close collaboration enables better projects for our clients. In our team deliveries, we can get support from Databricks to ensure quality architecture and better end result.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are also partners with other technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want!
Archicture is highly valued at Capgemini, and therefore we’ve invested a lot in educational architecture programs and communities where architects can share and develop ideas. So, if you’re interested in becoming an either a solutition architect or entreprise architecture, we have learning communities for you.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Spark, Pandas or Azure Data Factory
Experience with the Databricks Lakehouse Architecture
Good understanding of the Databricks Platform
Excellent Python skills
Excellent SQL skills
Good Spark skills
Good skills in DevOps processes with git version control and CI/CD practices
Good communications skills
Ability to work well in a team
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Databricks: Delta Live Tables
Databricks: Unity Catalog
Software Engineering
Experienced with streaming systems
Data Modelling (Data Vault, Star Schema etc)
Test Automation
Experience with setting up Azure, AWS or GCP Infrastructure
Infrastructure as Code tools such as Terraform or Biceps
Spark Query Optimization techniques

Title: Data Engineer / Data Scientist till Preem
Description:
Nu har du möjlighet att bli pionjär i Preems nyligen etablerade dataplattform och skapa värde för verksamheten och omvärlden genom data. Haka på deras digitala transformation och bli en viktig del i resan mot en grönare framtid. Vi söker en Data Engineer / Data Scientist med passion för problemlösning och intresse för Databricks, Machine Learning och Big Data.
Om rollen
I rollen som Data Engineer / Data Scientist kommer du få vara en del av Preems storsatsning till att höja datakvalitén och bli mer datadrivna. Du kommer ha en central roll i att utveckla och implementera initiativ kopplat till data. Arbetet rör ett framväxande funktionsområe inom företaget och det finns stort utrymme att ingå i de arkitekturella frågeställningarna och besluten.
Du kommer vara en del i ett team tillsammans med utvecklare, lösnings- och
informationsarkitekter vars uppgifter är att säkerställa en kontrollerad och fungerande helhet gällande IT-arkitektur, Information Management och Masterdata Management.
Huvudsakliga arbetsuppgifter:
Bygga och underhålla den koncerngemensamma dataplattformen (Databricks i Azure)
Optimera data pipelines
Möjliggöra snabb och pålitlig dataåtkomst
Utföra avancerade analyser av data för att hitta mönster och generera insikter för att
fatta bättre affärsbeslut
Etablera, utveckla och förvalta machine learning
Du blir en viktig del av Preem – en arbetsplats som präglas av välkomnande stämning, förtroende för medarbetarna och ambitionen att vara bäst i branschen när det gäller hållbarhet. Här får du frihet under ansvar och ofta chansen att vara med under hela processen – från början till slut. Ansvarstagande, nyskapande och inkluderande värderas högt på Preem och genomsyrar allt arbete. Därför är det viktigt att du delar samma uppfattning.


Rollen är en heltidstjänst till Preems huvudkontor i Stockholm. Preem har en hybrid work-model där du kan arbeta på distans hälften av din arbetstid. Du rapporterar till chefen för Digital, BI & Governance.


Är det här du?
Vi söker dig som är en passionerad problemlösare med intresse för att använda data för att lösa affärsproblem och förbättra verksamheter. Vi ser gärna att du arbetet med Azure Databricks, Machine Learning och Big Data-teknologier.


För att lyckas i rollen är det viktigt att du har god samarbetsförmåga, är initiativtagande och har ett flexibelt förhållningssätt. Vi kommer att lägga stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper.


Du har:
Erfarenhet av att jobba med Data Engineering och/eller Data Science
Goda kunskaper i programmering, särskilt i SQL och Python med tillhörande
bibliotek och ramverk
God konceptuell förståelse för maskininlärning
Erfarenhet av DevOps-processer
Bekantskap med olika databaser och datalagringssystem
Akademisk examen inom datavetenskap, statistik, matematik eller liknande


Meriterande:
Erfarenhet av att arbeta tillsammans med kravställare på data för BI- och
OI-rapportering
Insikt i de arkitekturella vägval som är aktuella i implementationen av en
dataplattform med Lake house-struktur
Fördjupad förståelse av maskininlärning
Databricks och relaterade verktyg
Big Data-teknologier
Erfarenhet av MLOps och CI/CD


Rollen kräver att man kan kommunicera obehindrat i tal och skrift både på svenska och engelska.
Intresserad av att ansöka eller få veta mer?
I denna rekrytering samarbetar Preem med IDG Recruitment. Vid intresse eller frågor kontakta Moa Eriksson, Rekryteringskonsult på 070 828 36 65, moa.eriksson@idg.se eller Maria Widegren, Rekryteringskonsult 073 423 15 50, maria.widegren@idg.se


För att ansöka, vänligen skicka in ditt CV eller ansök med Linkedin.


Om Preem
Vi är Preem, Sveriges största drivmedelsbolag. Vi har en vision om att leda
omvandlingen mot ett hållbart samhälle genom att bli klimatneutrala i hela
värdekedjan, från utvinning av råvaror till produktion och försäljning. Senast år 2030 ska Preem producera 5 miljoner kubikmeter förnybara drivmedel, och senast 2035 ska vi vara klimatneutrala i hela värdekedjan. Preems raffinaderier räknas till de mest moderna och miljöanpassade i Europa med en raffineringskapacitet på över 18 miljoner kubikmeter per år. Vår verksamhet omfattar produktion, försäljning, distribution samt trading och varuförsörjning. Vi förädlar och säljer drivmedel, eldnings- och smörjolja samt andra produkter till företag och privatpersoner. Vi har ett rikstäckande servicenät med drygt 520 tankställen för privat- och yrkestrafik. Preem AB har drygt 1 500 anställda varav 950 arbetar vid raffinaderierna. För helåret 2020 var Preems omsättning 68,2 miljarder SEK.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
Machine Learning Engineer
Our Business Intelligence & Analytics team is providing consulting services to clients in the Nordic region from our office in Stockholm based on the latest technology leading platform providers such as Microsoft, Amazon and Google. The demand around cloud based analytical platforms is constantly growing and we are now looking for candidates with strong technical competence and a can-do attitude. You will take part in our client implementation projects to help and guide our clients to become more data-driven and AI-driven.
The team you will be joining is responsible for delivering an end-to-end Machine Learning solution, from building MLOps platform, model training to machine learning powered software development.
As a Machine Learning Engineer, you will apply your knowledge of data science, machine learning and software engineering to implement and run machine learning workloads on Cloud; in particular, using Databricks and Azure Machine Learning Service. This entails planning and creating a suitable working environment for machine learning workloads on Azure, running experiments and training models, managing, deploying and monitoring machine learning models in production.
Requirements
University Degree from Computer Science, Software Engineering, Mathematics or equivalent
Preferably 1-3 years of experience as Machine Learning Engineer, Data Scientist, Software Engineer, or DevOps Engineer
Knowledge of machine learning algorithms and practical experience of machine learning model development
Strong software development skills and proficiency in one or more programming languages, e.g., Python, Scala, C++

Preferably, you have
Experience of using machine learning platforms like MLflow
Experience of development with Git and Shell under Linux
Familiar with Databricks, Azure Machine Learning and Data Lake
Experience in technical consulting projects
Fluent in English and good communication skills
Swedish on conversation level is beneficial
You are
Social team-player with drive and positive attitude
Analytical and driven
A person with “Can-do mentality”
You would like to work with us if you
Want to work with the latest technology and projects within in Analytics and AI
Are motivated by customer challenges
Like to work in teams and are humble

Pension
Healthcare allowance
Skills development
Monthly social activities
Joint out of work activities and annual adventures

Title: Norwegian Speaking Customer Service Agent
Description:
Customer Service Agent - Norway
THE OPPORTUNITY
Do you have an interest in fashion, see solutions rather than problems and always strive to provide service at a top level? Then this opportunity might be the one for you.
Do you also value a dynamic and international work environment, fun and knowledgeable colleagues as well as a lot of internal career opportunities, then apply and get the chance to join our amazing Customer Service Team.
As our new Customer Service Agent you will join a team, where you together will work towards providing world class service to our customers.

WHAT YOU WILL DO
The first part of your journey at Boozt will be to take part in a thorough training program to create the best possible conditions for you to succeed and excel in your new role. Training sessions and development meetings will be held continuously throughout your time at Boozt.
Together with our trainers you will focus on your development and take part in training sessions to tailor your journey as a Boozter.
Provide top class service to our customers with all inquiries coming in via phone, email or chat
Be our expert when it comes to questions ranging from specific product information, to styling tips, stock status, shipping details, payment queries, and campaign errands
You will be the company’s eyes and ears and will be a truly important part of the “from order to delivery chain” to ensure that we reach our goal of building an unrivaled customer experience

YOUR PROFILE
You speak and write fluently in Norwegian.
You are also fluent in English since this is our corporate language and it is a part of your daily tasks to support other markets when needed
You enjoy solving problems, exceeding expectations and has a natural ability to connect with people
You see no obstacles in the challenges of offering quick, informative and individual answers and explanations even in stressful times
Previous experience in the service industry is a plus
Good communication skills and a real interest in expressing yourself well, both in speech and writing (tests will be given as part of our recruitment process)
You are proud of being precise and it is natural for you to be considerate in your behavior both internally and externally

OUR OFFER
This is a chance for you to join our vibrant Customer Service Team, an opportunity to grow and develop with one of the leading Nordic E-commerce companies
Full-time temporary employment for an initial 12 months with the possibility for a permanent position (the employment will start with a 6 month probation period)
Working hours for the Norwegian teams are 8:00-17:00 and 10:00-19:00 on a rolling schedule.
Your working schedule will be published for you to see four months in advance
You will join a big international team where we support and learn from each other, but the most important of all we have fun while doing so

Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.

We look forward to your application!

BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?

We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.

Title: Country Manager | Norway
Description:
THE OPPORTUNITY

Over the past 10 years, Boozt.com has grown to become the leading Nordic Department store. To strengthen the Boozt brand’s local visibility and for our core markets to grow further we are looking for a team of Country Managers for Norway, Denmark and Sweden.
As a Country Manager for Norway you will be part of a team of Country Managers and be responsible for the Norwegian market. Your primary responsibility will be the P&L for the country ensuring that the revenue targets are met while continuously strengthening our brand and position in the market.
You will work closely with the core commercial teams such as Category Management, CRM, Media, BI, Brand & Visual Communication as well as Buying & Merchandising.
We offer the flexibility of working remotely for this position, with mandatory visits to the Headquarter in Malmö approximately 4-6 days a month and you will report to our Country & Category Director.


WHAT YOU WILL DO
As our Norwegian Country Manager you will be responsible for ensuring that the Norwegian customers have the best possible shopping experience and you will act as their ambassador. You will set the local strategy and make sure that we execute accordingly, i.e.

Own the local P&L, meeting revenue targets and balancing marketing costs
Together with the core teams you will create and execute marketing and media strategies as well as localizing the daily trade plan and driving the seasonal local activities and campaigns
Monitor the daily operations, making sure that we live up to our standards
Perform a variety of analysis and prepare, implement and monitor new strategic and operational initiatives for the Norwegian market


YOUR PROFILE
We are looking for an experienced Business Director or Media Director with great experience within Marketing and with a proven track record of building a brand. To be successful in this role you need to have an in-depth understanding of the Norwegian market, especially the media landscape.
At Boozt we have a care-why-mindset and are looking for a colleague with a creative and challenging attitude, one who thrives in a fast-paced environment and with a passion for improvements and sales.

5+ years of senior marketing experience, e.g. as a Business or Media Director from the Media Agency business or as a Brand Manager for a brand that operates across markets
Strong business & commercial mindset, self-driven, structured, and proactive
Bachelor or Masters degree in Business, Marketing, Media or equivalent field

Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.
