Title: GIS-specialist
Description:
Mellersta militärregionen (MR M) är ett krigsförband lokaliserat i Upplands Bro kommun, närmare bestämt i Kungsängen. Staben består av kontinuerligt tjänstgörande officerare samt civila. Vid höjd beredskap kompletteras staben med tillfälligt tjänstgörande.


Chefen för Mellersta militärregionen med regional stab leder underställda förband, samverkar med regionala och lokala aktörer, leder säkerhets- och underrättelsetjänsten samt stödjer operativ- och taktisk chef som löser uppgifter inom regionen. MR M omfattar Dalarnas-, Gävleborgs-, Västmanlands-, Uppsalas-, Stockholms- och Södermanlands län. MR M är en egen organisationsenhet med ansvar för både insats- och produktionsledning för bl.a. utbildningsgrupper och hemvärn.

Vi söker nu en GIS-specialist/ingenjör som vill vara med och utveckla den Mellersta Militärregionen.

Vi söker medarbetare för att bemanna ett team som skall ansvara för att utveckla användning och utarbetande samt visualisering av digitala geografiska underlag.
Arbetslaget du ingår i skall vidareutveckla användningen av GIS som visualiserings- och planeringsverktyg. Tillsammans med engagerade och kunniga kollegor bidrar du till att utveckla förmågan att skapa underlag för planering och beslut.
Din huvudsakliga uppgift är att utveckla användningen av geografisk data för att därigenom öka MR M effekt. Detta möjliggörs genom att arbeta verksamhetsintegrerat med sakkunniga för att med utgångspunkt från olika datamängder kunna skapa informations- och beslutsunderlag för MR M chefer.
Tjänsten innebär därför att du kommer arbeta med beredning av ärenden, inhämtning, strukturering, implementering och visualisering av stora mängder data.
Du förväntas kunna driva frågor självständigt men kommer ingå i ett team med helhetsansvar

Kvalifikationer
Högskoleutbildning med inriktning på datateknik, datalogi, systemvetenskap, data science, systemvetenskap eller lång arbetslivserfarenhet inom liknande områden.
God förmåga att uttrycka dig i tal och skrift på svenska och engelska.

Meriterande
Erfarenhet av ESRI-plattformen och databashantering.
Erfarenhet och engagemang av ajourhållning av geodata.
Erfarenhet av arbete med geodatanalys.
Erfarenhet av militär underrättelsetjänst.
Erfarenhet av arbete med IT-system som hanterar försvarssekretess i de högre säkerhetsnivåerna.
Erfarenhet av kvalitetsarbete inom GIS.
Erfarenhet av Carmenta-plattformen.
Erfarenhet av programmering i Python.


Övrigt
Tjänsten är öppen att söka för civila medarbetare.
Tjänsten är tillsvidare med tillträde snarast.
Tjänsten är placerad i säkerhetsskyddsklass.
Praktiska prov och tester kommer att ske som en del av urvalsprocessen.
Arbetsort är Stockholm, Upplands-Bro, Kungsängen.

Upplysning om tjänsten kan lämnas av
MR M J2, Dragi Ilic, vilken nås via växeln på 08-584 540 00

Fackliga representanter
OFR/O Livgardet Stefan Morin
SEKO Lise-Lott Larsson
SACO Johan Gillemyr
OFR/S Kenneth Hartikainen
Samtliga nås via växeln på 08-584 540 00
Välkommen med din ansökan senast 2023-01-31. Din ansökan skall innehålla CV samt ett personligt brev.

Title: Data Scientist
Description:
Cure Media has been announced as one of the Top Influencer Marketing companies by Business of Apps in the UK, three years in a row!

As the power is shifting from companies to consumers, our mission is to help brands talk to their audience on their terms, by leveraging leading influencer channels that people trust and follow in their everyday lives. We’re growing fast and are now looking for a Data Scientist to join us on our journey to becoming the first choice for brands and influencers in Europe!
We are looking for a Data Scientist with experience and passion in advanced data analysis. Someone that is self-reliable and interested in consumer marketing behaviors. You should be interested in complex tasks and to explore new innovative solutions. As a data scientist you will continue the work to implement machine learning to predict which influencers that should be used in our campaigns. Insights that will be shared within the team and other departments in the company.
Cure Media is working with thousands of influencers in several markets such as the Nordics, Germany and the UK. This means that we also need to make trend reports on how influencer marketing differentiates between different countries.
What we offer:
The opportunity to become a partner through a stock option program.
The possibility to work with one of the fastest growing marketing channels globally, at a company in the forefront of the industry.
The role is new so you will have a big role in shaping and developing it together with our CPO.
The opportunity to play a key role in our international expansion and become part of a high-performing tech team.
We think you have:
A degree in statistics, mathematics, data science or equivalent
Experience and passion for modeling/machine learning
Good knowledge in visualizing and presenting actionable insights
Speak and write fluently in Swedish and English
Also, we think you have competencies in the following:
Python, TensorFlow, Pandas, Matplotlib, Apache, Spark, HDFS, Tidyverse, Ggplot, SQL, MongoDB
Other perks & benefits:
6 weeks paid vacation per year
Generous health package and training during working hours, e.g. Padel
MacBook and iPhone
Breakfast together every Monday
Annual conference trip
Start: ASAP (full-time)
Location & Reporting: You’ll be based in Stockholm as part of our Stockholm office and report to our founder and CPO.
Do you have any questions about the role, the career development opportunities, or something else? Get in touch with us!
Please note that the application should be in English.

Title: Finance Business Partner
Description:
IQVIA is a worldwide top 10 Fortune 500 company, active in Life Sciences. With the merger of Quintiles and IMS Health, IQVIA combines clinical research with a broader use of health data and technology. IQVIA’s data and technology are increasingly used for answering socially relevant questions related to healthcare efficiency, quality and accessibility. With almost 80.000 employees, IQVIA has an increasing contribution to the development of sustainable health systems worldwide and on a regional level.
Finance Business Partner
In this role you will report to the Director of Finance & Operations and will be responsible for managing the IQVIA Nordics commercial operations processes for Real World Analytics & Healthcare. This includes ownership of in-quarter/full year revenue & profitability management and forecasting, design and provision of financial and operational analysis and reporting to meet both country and regional requirements. You will be working closely with the sales and delivery teams to ensure business objectives are achieved.

Responsibilities:
Leading of the quarter-end revenue close process and the profitability process & initiative.
Ensuring visibility to the business of requirements and delivery risks.
Acts as a link between the sales, delivery, and sales admin teams to ensure issues affecting quarter end revenue recognition are identified and resolved.
Monthly reviews of NDS Real World Analytics & healthcare projects.
Owns the fortnightly in-quarter & monthly FY revenue & profitability forecasting process to ensure full transparency of business leads to performance
Ensures that the recording, measurement, and reporting of all financial transactions adhere to generally accepted accounting principles (US GAAP), internal IQVIA corporate policies and procedures, government regulations and local business/functional requirements. Supports complex and large deals within the region with deal structure and contacting to ensure efficient and compliant revenue recognition.
Provides training sessions for new PMs on operating procedures.
Works closely with Finance / P&L leads to gain understanding of project profitability, on all open projects across the Healthcare / RWS portfolio.
Ad-hoc:
Creates CRM Reporting & Dashboards
Involvement on EMEA Finance & commercial operations/Operational Excellence initiatives

Who are you?
Proven experience in similar business/commercial analysis and finance roles
Graduate degree or equivalent in Finance, Accounting or Financial Management
Working knowledge of financial systems (SAP/Hyperion/SFDC), local regulations and US GAAP
Technical proficiency with financial application software is essential, as well as sound knowledge of Microsoft tools (especially Excel and PowerPoint)
Excellent oral and written communication skills (mainly in English)
Strong project management skills and ability to translate business issues into financial requirements
Personality:
Analytical mindset
Open minded and business focused
Ability to influence outcomes
Excellent team player
#LI-SABINESTERCKX
IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions and clinical research services to the life sciences industry. We believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com

Title: Backend Developer
Description:
Oneflow is a rapidly growing tech scale-up located in the heart of Stockholm. We have created a platform that automates the entire contract process from start to finish, all in one place. Turning clunky, static contracts into customer-oriented, digital contracts that feel like magic.

The team
You will be working with the Oneflow product, mostly written in Python and React, where we make several deployments each day and continuously improve our product. We are self-organizing teams that like to discuss how to approach and break down problems together and value data-driven decisions. We want our developers to feel a strong sense of ownership and that their work really matters. We also want them to be involved in all steps of product development, from feature planning to release.

Who you are
As a Backend Developer at Oneflow, you have an interest in distributed systems and their scalability. You will mainly work with Python or Java development and will both improve existing flows and create new ones as our product evolves, to meet customer needs while staying performant and reliable. We see that you have at least a few years of experience working with backends for web applications written in Python. If you are good at SQL queries and know some things about deployment pipelines that would definitely be an advantage.
Your background
Having worked at least a few years as a backend developer
Experience of working with Python
A good understanding of SQL databases
An interest in REST API design
Knowledge of some cloud APIs (AWS, Azure etc.)
Technologies to work with
Python
Flask
Celery
MySQL
Elasticsearch
Docker
We also value if you have an interest in either of these areas:
Security
Infrastructure
Data science (statistics, machine learning, etc)
Distributed logging
How we work
We want our employees to feel a strong sense of ownership, to feel like what they do really matters, and to be involved in all steps of product development, from feature planning to release. Our team and culture are built on this principle of inclusion and responsibility, which we see as crucial in building a great product.
We strive for a truly agile development environment that promotes getting things done, rather than focusing too much on processes and enterprise tools. This means we typically work in short iterations, regularly going from conceptual discussions to shipped product features in a few weeks. We believe early and honest feedback is the best feedback, both internally and from our customers.
We value gender equality and diversity in our organization and therefore, we strive for a team that reflects the diversity in today's society.
Come work with us
At Oneflow we welcome everyone and we do our recruitment based on competencies. If you feel the above description seems like a good fit for you - we would love to hear from you! Get in touch to start a journey you won’t forget!
Our recruitment process starts with Emese from the People & Culture team. After her interview, you will complete a personality and logic test set by our partner Alva Labs, and then complete an assignment which will showcase a sample of your work before the technical interview.
Apply by submitting your resume and personal letter telling us more about why the role is interesting and why you would be a good fit. We will get back to you as soon as possible!

Visit our website for more information about our product and Oneflow. Visit our blog for more information about our culture and future colleagues

Title: Tax Data Analyst
Description:
Nasdaq is now looking for a Tax/Transfer Pricing Data Technology Analyst to join the global Tax team. In this role, you will work mainly with Transfer Pricing, being involved in implementing and improving data processes and technology related to Transfer Pricing and Tax within Nasdaq.
The position is located in Stockholm, Sweden.
Nasdaq has business operations in over 30 countries, and we expand our business through organic growth and acquisitions worldwide. Being part of the international Tax team means you will work closely with colleagues in Stockholm, New York, Bangalore and Sydney as well as with the Business and Accounting teams.
About Nasdaq
Nasdaq is a leading global provider of trading, clearing, exchange technology, listing, information and public company services across six continents. Our technology powers more than 90 marketplaces in 50 countries.
Here, you will work for a global tech leader committed to breaking down barriers to inclusive prosperity. We see technology as a way to allow people to work together more productively and effectively by centralizing data, analytics, and market intelligence.
We’re committed to building a more diverse and inclusive workforce. Not only is it our responsibility to do better, but we also need representative voices to power the fresh thinking that is vital for our business and our clients.
Role and Responsibilities
To be successful in this position, you must have an interest in data, processes and technology and like to translate that in to the exciting world of transfer pricing. We hope you are keen to analyze our tax data! You will be involved in identifying opportunities to improve processes related to tax/accounting information.
You Will Bring
Bachelor of Science degree in business administration, accounting, computer science, data science or equivalent
2-5 years of professional experience within transfer pricing, tax or financial accounting from an international organization
Expertise in Microsoft Office Products, excellent skills in Microsoft Excel
You should be an analytical and ambitious person, who can work independently
Good communication skills in written and spoken English
Would be great if you have
Proficiency with any of the accounting systems, Workday Financials or Hyperion Essbase (SmartView)
Some experience with data transformation tools such as Power BI, Alteryx
Some experience with operational tax/transfer pricing technology products such as Longview
Does This Sound Like You?
We offer a full-time position located in Stockholm, Sweden. As we will start reviewing resumes February 1st, please submit your application in English as soon as possible.
At Nasdaq, we provide our employees with the resources and opportunities they need to chart a career of achievement along with a strong compensation package that includes annual bonus opportunity, equity grants, as well as an employee stock purchase program. Nasdaq Sweden provides its employees 32 days of annual vacation (plus 1 additional flex day every two months), health insurance, career development programs, and more. We advocate flexible ways of working and have a hybrid work model.
Come as You Are
Nasdaq is an equal opportunity employer. We positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of age, color, disability, national origin, ancestry, race, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, veteran status, genetic information, or any other status protected by applicable law.
We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request an accommodation.

Title: CTA DLM Office based Sweden
Description:
Job Overview
The Clinical Functional Service Partnerships (CFSP) Project Team are responsible for the management of multiple global projects for assigned clients and serve as key operational finance contact points. The team is also involved in supporting the strategic decisions of the business by partnering with operational teams to develop and interpret analytical data models.
The CFSP Project Manager is accountable for the Financial and Contractual oversight of assigned projects and ensures all reporting activities are accurate and prepared within established timelines.

Essential Functions
Completion of month end activities and provide global variance explanations to forecast
Revenue recognition for all projects under client portfolio
Oversight of invoicing for fees and expenses for all projects
Backlog phasing and adjustments for all projects
Conduct monthly review and analysis of assigned projects, including review of revenue recognition, project performance variances, contract opportunities and ad-hoc financial analysis as required
Monitor project and customer activity against contract terms to ensure compliance from operational teams and the customer
Collaborate with operational teams to ensure consistency in contract preparation
Align with Contracts, Legal and Strategic Pricing as appropriate
Co-ordinate with Project Finance and Global Finance as appropriate to implement process improvements
Review forecasting requirements from customer
Attend and prepare for monthly reviews
Defend financial performance at the Finance review calls; proactively participate in discussions to identify, communicate and address financial issues
Partner with the Operational Excellence Lead and Model Alliance Lead to align on messaging
Support in Business Review deliverables (Supply vs Demand, Volatility reporting)
Meet Global Finance reporting needs (forecasting, anticipated revenue, variance analysis, ad-hoc requests)
Attend Operational Reviews as needed; share finance results and key messages
Act as key point of contact for customer counterpart(s)
Meet customer reporting deliverables and deadlines
Work closely to ensure timely invoice payment (investigate causes for aged debt)
Involvement/Leading initiatives and workstreams to investigate and implement improvements to processes
Support and training to Operational teams (DLMs, ROLs, other) and prep/update of guidance tools
Perform other duties as required

Qualifications
Bachelor's Degree
Experience in a CRO or Pharma in a PM type capacity Req
Strong communication skills (verbal and written)
Excellent organization, interpersonal, teamwork skills with exceptional attention to detail and accuracy
Positive attitude and ability to interact with all levels of staff
Ability to manage multiple priorities to meet deadlines as necessary
Proficient in Microsoft Excel and experience with Peoplesoft preferred
Willingness to work in a flexible and challenging environment
IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions and clinical research services to the life sciences industry. We believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com

Title: Data Engineer som vill skapa framtida historia
Description:
Hej!
Vilken framtida historia vill du skapa?

Vi på Artificial Collective
vill skapa framtida historia med AI och förbättra vardagen för miljarder människor, varelser och vår planet inom det kommande decenniet!
Det är vår vision, och den är stor!
Men vi är på god väg då vi idag samarbetar med några av Nordens mest spännande företag där vi tillsammans med de mest passionerade inom AI/Data, inspirerar vi varandra varje dag och riktar vår samlade kunskap mot att skapa de bästa AI-lösningarna som bidrar med en större nytta.

Bli en del av teamet ‍‍
som idag består av seniora kollegor inom Data Science och Machine Learning. För att fortsätta arbeta med de mest spännande projekten, söker vi just nu efter vår nästa kollega inom Data Engineering.
Som anställd eller egen konsult hos Artificial Collective får du möjligheten att arbeta med just det ditt hjärta bultar extra för. Både i individuella och i teamprojekt.
Du själv bestämmer över din tid, ersättning, vad du vill arbeta med och i vilken riktning du vill utvecklas. Istället för en gammeldags hierarki med konsultchefer, får du som en del av Artificial Collective, en dedikerad agent som tillsammans med dig ser till att du kommer dit! Exempelvis genom utbildning, inspiration eller med hjälp av mentorskap från en expert inom önskat område.
Vi söker inte enbart efter någon som har rätt teknisk bakgrund, utan någon som vill vara med och fortsätta forma Artificial Collective till det bästa möjliga, med och för oss alla.


Vi tror att du brinner för
Utveckla, strukturera och optimera datapipelines, ETL-processer, datalager och molninfrastruktur.
Arbeta tillsammans med verksamheten för att säkerställa att vi förstår och tillhandahåller rätt data till våra slutanvändare.
Intresse för att hantera större datamängder och visualisera samt presentera datadrivna insikter.
Utmärkta SQL-kunskaper och goda programmeringskunskaper inom Python eller liknande.

Vårt löfte
är att ge dig vad du behöver för att du ska kunna lägga mer tid på det som ditt hjärta bultar extra för!
Vi tror på frihet och att det skapar välmående vilket vi ser som avgörande för passion samt geniala idéer.
Vi tror på passion och att det är viktigt för glädje och fortsatt lärande. Vi vill frigöra din passion.
‍‍ Vi tror på styrkan i att arbeta tillsammans och rikta vår kollektiva passion mot visionära idéer och skapa bättre lösningar.
Samtidigt får du det bästa paketet av förmåner.
Lön: 40-80k/månad
Semester: 30-60 betalda dagar
Pension: Ja
Försäkringar: Ja
Friskvård: Ja

Visst låter det intressant?
Sök direkt och var med och skapa den framtida historian du vill se när vi tillsammans tar nästa stora steg inom AI!

Title: Engineering Data Analyst
Description:
We are looking to grow the data capability at our first gigafactory in Skellefteå, Sweden. Our factories produce large amounts of heterogenous data that get uploaded to our cloud platform, and are then processed, organized, and ready for analysis. You will partner cross-functionally with the Engineering, Production and Quality teams in Skellefteå to drive data-driven manufacturing operations.
As an Engineering Data Analyst, you will contribute directly to solving problems, lead discovery of insights, and build a shared knowledge base. We strive to use technology and data to co-develop solutions that matter, and welcome applicants from diverse experience levels and backgrounds.
We are searching for someone passionate about using data visualization, statistics, and modeling to tell stories and support decisions. The ideal candidate is a curious life-long learner who takes ownership and is eager to collaborate to build better products. This role is a vital member of the Ett Digitalization team is key to Northvolt's mission to enable the future of energy.
Key responsibilities include
Troubleshoot and root cause issues in the manufacturing operations
Build analytics solutions for production, quality, and engineering applications to drive Continuous Improvement projects
Validate generated data and drive data quality initiatives
Share knowledge of data tooling, dataset and analytics capabilities across technical and non-technical teams on-site in Skellefteå
Define requirements for enhancements of the Northvolt Data Science and Analytics Platform
Skills & Requirements
Preferred Experience
Communication, communication, communication. You communicate fluently and humbly with all types of different humans choosing effective methods based on context, audience and purpose.
Python: Data analysis and visualization (jupyter, pandas, matplotlib/seaborn/bokeh/plotly etc.)
Comfortable writing SQL queries
Not Required (bonus points)
[Bonus] Engineering foundation understanding (electro/mechanical/chemical/physical), preferably within the energy domain
[Bonus] Manufacture industry and/or Li-ion technology experience
[Bonus] Statistics, algorithms, clustering, uncertainty quantification
[Bonus] Analyzing and modeling time-series data and unstructured data
[Bonus] Data visualization using tools (e.g. Grafana, Kibana, PowerBI, Tableau, Qlik, Quicksight, etc.)
[Bonus] Software engineering (version control, unix, software workflow, either of C/C++/C#/Java/Go)

Independent, organized and entrepreneurial

Qualities that we value are flexibility, sense of quality, friendliness, motivation to take on new challenges, grit and a sense of humor
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment

Warrant program

Title: Förändringsledare inom AI som vill skapa framtida historia
Description:
Hej!

Hur vill du att framtiden ser ut?


Vi på Artificial Collective
vill skapa framtida historia med AI! Tillsammans med de mest passionerade inom AI/Data, inspirerar vi varandra varje dag och riktar vår samlade kunskap mot att skapa de bästa AI-lösningarna som bidrar med en större nytta. Både för samhället och enskilda företag.
Idag samarbetar vi med några av de mest spännande företagen i Norden!

Bli en del av teamet ‍‍
som idag består av seniora konsulter inom Data Science och Machine Learning. För att fortsätta arbeta med de mest spännande projekten, söker vi just nu efter vår nästa kollega som Förändringsledare.
Som anställd eller egen konsult hos Artificial Collective får du möjligheten att arbeta med just det ditt hjärta bultar extra för, oavsett om det gäller nyutveckling, vidareutveckling eller förvaltning. Både i individuella och i teamprojekt.
Du själv bestämmer över din tid, ersättning, vad du vill arbeta med och i vilken riktning du vill utvecklas. Som en del av Artificial Collective, får du en dedikerad agent som tillsammans med dig ser till att du kommer dit! Exempelvis genom utbildning, inspiration eller med hjälp av mentorskap från en expert inom önskat område.

Vi tror att du brinner för

Potentialen hos data och hur AI/ML kan skapa nytta i olika verksamheter.
Sprida kunskaper kring möjligheter, utmaningar och förutsättningar för att nyttja data på rätt sätt.

Stötta företag i deras resa att bli AI-moget och ta till sig ett AI-drivet arbetssätt.
Design och tillämpning av maskininlärning eller statistiska modeller.

Implementera olika modeller i nya och befintliga system av olika karaktär.

Vårt löfte
är att ge dig vad du behöver för att du ska kunna lägga mer tid på det som ditt hjärta bultar extra för!
Vi tror på frihet och att det skapar välmående vilket vi ser som avgörande för passion samt geniala idéer.
Vi tror på passion och att det är viktigt för glädje och fortsatt lärande. Vi vill frigöra din passion.
‍‍ Vi tror på styrkan i att arbeta tillsammans och rikta vår kollektiva passion mot visionära idéer och skapa bättre lösningar.
Samtidigt får du det bästa paketet av förmåner.
Lön: 40-80k/månad
Semester: 30-60 betalda dagar
Pension: Ja
Försäkringar: Ja
Friskvård: Ja

Visst låter det intressant?
Sök direkt och var med och skapa den framtida historian du vill se när vi tillsammans tar nästa stora steg inom AI!

Title: Experienced Data Scientist/ Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
Lockas du av en roll där du får möjlighet att bistå uppdragsgivare med datadriven affärs- och verksamhetsutveckling hela vägen från strategiska vägval till implementerad lösning och realiserad nytta? I din roll som ML Engineer kommer du med hjälp av data och maskininlärning ta våra kunder in i framtiden.
Om rollen:
Vår utgångspunkt är alltid i verksamhetsfrågorna och du kommer att vara en nyckelspelare i hela kedjan från Data Engineering, via Data Science-modeller, till produktionsättning och modellförvaltning. Dessutom kommer du ofta att inkluderas i projektens tidigare faser; från affärs- och dataförståelse till data science-prototyper.
Tillämpningsområdet är brett; från att göra prognoser på antal besökare till nöjesparker till att varna för anomalier i fakturor och optimera direktreklam. Vad gäller Machine Learning Engineering så har vi stort fokus på Databricks och jobbar i första hand med molntjänsterna Azure, AWS och Google Cloud Platform.
Mer om oss:
Capgemini, Insights & Data, är Nordens riktmärke inom Data, AI och Analytics. Vi är över 300 anställda, fördelade på våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg, Malmö och Helsingborg. Våra tjänster inkluderar konsultverksamhet inom Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services och Solution Services. Många av marknadens främsta experter arbetar med oss, vilket sätter oss i bästa möjliga position att hjälpa våra kunder att lyckas i sin resa mot datadrivna beslut. Vår storlek på den nordiska marknaden ger oss kompetens och kapacitet att verkligen göra skillnad för våra kunder, och erbjuda alltifrån lokala projekt till större globala utrullningar.
Vem du är:
Flerårig erfarenhet i rollen som Data Scientist/ ML Engineer
Goda kunskaper i Python och tillämpning av Dataanalys och Machine Learning i Python med relevanta paket (ex. Pandas, scikit, pytorch)
Du har en pedagogisk förmåga och kan förklara Data Science på ett lättbegripligt sätt
Akademisk bakgrund inom matematik/ingenjör/IT med inriktning mot data eller har en bakgrund som mjukvaruutvecklare som har gått mot Data Science
Goda kunskaper i såväl svenska som engelska
Meriterande erfarenhet:
Databricks
Förståelse för livscykeln för Data Science-lösningar; från idé till produktionsatta modeller i drift
Produktionssättning av Machine Learning-lösningar och verktyg för MLOps (CI/CD och continious training) i Azure, AWS och/eller Google Cloud Platform
Använt mjukvaruutvecklingsverktyg som Docker för att paketera lösningar i stabila miljöer
Förståelse för övergripande plattformar och arkitektfrågor
Bra affärsförståelse, då du behöver kunna förstå våra uppdragsgivares utmaningar, inte bara de tekniska utmaningarna
Kunskaper om kringliggande fält, som Data Engineering och Business Intelligence
Som person är du driven, verksamhetsorienterad och du trivs lika bra med att arbeta självständigt som i grupp. Du sätter stort fokus på dialogen med kund, men är även intresserad av att engagera dig i att utveckla oss till att bli en ännu bättre arbetsplats. Det är viktigt att du är analytisk, lösningsorienterad och nyfiken, har en god samarbetsförmåga och lätt för att kommunicera. Därtill är det meriterande om du har erfarenhet av eller intresse för att hålla utbildningar och workshops. Det är viktigt att du behärskar svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift eftersom vi har en nära dialog med våra kunder.

Title: Consultant - with focus on e-commerce/data driven marketing
Description:
Who We Are

Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we work closely with clients to embrace a transformational approach aimed at benefiting all stakeholders—empowering organizations to grow, build sustainable competitive advantage, and drive positive societal impact.

Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives that question the status quo and spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting, technology and design, and corporate and digital ventures. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, fueled by the goal of helping our clients thrive and enabling them to make the world a better place.

Practice Area Profile

BCG’s Marketing, Sales & Pricing (MSP) Practice leverages deep customer insight and a powerful arsenal of data, tools & analytics to inspire revolutionary thinking in all aspects of marketing, sales and pricing. As such you will also work closely with our Technology, Data science & AI, Supply chain & Operations practices. We help digitally transform how clients go to market and generate significant value.

The foundation of our success continues to be outstanding value created for even the most leading of our clients. We seek to be cutting-edge and continue to invest in arsenal of tools and proprietary data. Through working on state-of-the-art solutions within eCom and data-driven marketing, you will be challenged out of your comfort zone, significantly widen your scope of expertise. With our strong sector expertise in consumer goods, especially fashion, luxury and retail, you will be able to work and learn from leading global companies and experts.

What You'll Do

As a Consultant within BCG’s focus on eCom and DDM, you will be a core member of our functional practice working alongside some of the world’s top minds in industry – supporting them in through transformation into digital landscape. You will collaborate on challenging projects with team members from many backgrounds, advising clients on a variety of topics.

What You'll Bring (Experience & Qualifications)

Strong academics from top-tier institution
4-7 years’ experience with a leading strategy consulting ﬁrm (focused on CRM, digital marketing & personalization, e-com) or digital company
Experience working in retail and/or FMCG and/or other consumer related industries is a plus
A strong consulting skillset: creative and hypothesis-led problem solving, framing, and communicating complex ideas, thinking strategically, excellent numerical skills
Fluency in English required, Swedish is a plus


Who You'll Work With
When you join BCG’s Stockholm office, you will work for the strategy consulting leader in Sweden and at one of our most prominent offices. Founded in 1989, BCG in Stockholm serves companies within the Swedish region and beyond. Since then, the business has grown rapidly. Our office is located in an 18th-century building, overlooking the Royal Opera and the Royal Castle, right in the heart of Stockholm. We have clients in a wide range of sectors, including financial services, technology and communications, industrial goods, consumer goods, and health care. The team at BCG’s Stockholm office is made up of individuals from very diverse backgrounds.

WE OFFER
Attractive and performance-based compensation package with fixed and variable components
Attractive insurance package
30 days of vacation
Sports and activities like padel and football
A wide variety of social office events
Social networks – Colorful@BCG, Pride@BCG, Women@BCG, Family@BCG

BCG offers professionals a chance to apply years of practice to new challenges. Across the business, experienced BCGers join the Group midcareer for many reasons—whether seeking more impact in their work or looking for a greater challenge. Meet our experienced professionals and read more about how to advance your career in new and meaningful ways here.

HOW TO APPLY
Please submit your application attaching your CV & Cover Letter through our BCG Career website. We process all applications we receive and screen them continuously. Please do not hesitate to apply even if you don’t meet all criteria as you might be suitable for future positions at BCG. We will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided accommodation to participate in the job application and interview process.

YOU’LL BE BASED IN
Stockholm, Sweden

TRAVEL REQUIRED
Yes

JOB TYPE
Full time

Title: Associate Director, Data Science
Description:
Associate Director, Data Science
Location: Mississauga (Canada), Gaithersburg (USA), Warsaw (Poland), Gothenburg (Sweden )

At AstraZeneca, we harness digital, data science & AI to fast-forward our research. Making sure work born in a lab can make a real difference. Everyday, impacting patients’ lives across the world.

Clinical Data and Insights (CDI) is a function of about 500 people within Development Operations. We work across the R&D portfolio and lead the delivery of clinical data and insights, through simplification, quality by design and collaboration. Our scope includes data management, centralized monitoring, trial safety review, standards, automation & specialist programming, transformational clinical data projects and data capability & operations. Our vision is to transform our clinical data flows and advance data derived insights, to enable acceleration of life changing medicines to patients.

As the Associate Director, Data Science you will be accountable for independently leading highly complex data science projects and/or leading project teams.You will be responsible for design, implementation and maintaining of production search systems/programs applying deep/machine learning and semantic engines over many content types (e.g. natural language, images, clinical data, entities/relationships). Work closely with data mangers and study teams to translate their requirements to products/solutions. Use various blends of analytical, data science and data wrangling skills to assess project objectives, understand the data and system landscape, design, build and deliver end-to-end solutions.
What you'll need to be successful in this role:
Deep understanding of modern vector/embedding-based representation techniques with the ability to design and implement algorithms for their generation
Deep knowledge of Tensorflow/Pytorch frameworks for implementing and optimizing deep learning algorithms for training quality and serving performance
Experience in industry or academic research, particularly in deep learning and neural networks
Strong algorithms, data structures, and coding background with either Python, C++, or Java programming experience
Experience working with knowledge graphs stores (Ontotext GraphDB, Neo4j) and surrounding semantic technology.
Proven experience of agile working practices
Proficient in building dashboards
Good organizational skills and the ability to multitask; set priorities and follow a timeline
Great attention to detail and excellent communications skills
Demonstrated ability to work in a fast-paced environment
Well-versed in leading a cross functional team as well as ability to work independently
Essential Requirements:
Bachelor’s or advanced degree in a Computer Science with proven track record as data scientist (US)
Proficient in data science and AI techniques, including Python, NLP Knowledge Graph, ML algorithms, with an ability to share insights in a powerful way.
In-depth experience in data analysis, profiling, investigating, interpreting and detailing data requirements, e.g. data modelling techniques and hands on modelling experience
Demonstrated data wrangling ability to combine data from disparate sources and generate insights

Accountabilities:
Acts as a subject matter expert in areas of data wrangling, data mining, data transformation, data visualization and data science and AI techniques, including predictive analytics to enable accelerated set up and conduct of data management activities and to a high-quality
Work closely with key business stakeholders to understand business need and deliver solutions that provides relevant data insights
Leads complex data science projects to generate knowledge and insights from clinical & operational data that help teams pause, reflect and be more efficient/effective in their data review tasks by eliminating non-value-added activities
Liaises closely with DM and programming teams to understand opportunities not covered by conventional data validation checks or data review reports and drives development of cutting-edge data management solutions
Builds effective partnership with data provisioning groups and data science representatives in the organization
Extended member of data strategy meeting chaired by study DM and advise teams on how best to utilize data to reduce redundancies and create efficiencies in data collection and review
Ability to identify business opportunities and discover new solutions that supports DM Leads/DMLT in achieving business objectives and operational efficiencies
Experienced in story telling with ability to communicate methodology and results to an audience of mixed technical backgrounds in an impactful way
Possess strong project management skills to lead an agile team with a value-focused culture
Guide teams to identify optimal model and effective ways to improve algorithms, performance runs, model tuning, experimentation and testing
Support and mentor other team members, may act as line manager
Provides consultancy and training in area of data analysis to other DM team members, including training on novel tools
Contributes to department strategy by acting as subject matter expert (internally and externally) and leading improvement and innovation projects


Desirable Requirements
Solid grasp of applied mathematical, machine learning and AI techniques and workflows
Good understanding of project management techniques and methods
Knowledge of statistics
Knowledge of pharmaceutical clinical research process
Knowledge of GxP & FAIR Data Principles

This position can be located in Mississauga (Canada), Gaitherburg (USA), Warsaw (Poland), Gothenburg (Sweden )

Benefits:
AstraZeneca is a leading company in the healthcare industry, with a mission to enrich the lives of others. It’s our business to support healthy living, not only for our patients, but also for our employees. Our benefits program is flexible enough to meet employees’ varying needs, offers valuable choices, and is highly competitive.

Why AstraZeneca?
At AstraZeneca when we see an opportunity for change, we seize it and make it happen, because any opportunity no matter how small, can be the start of something big. Delivering life-changing medicines is about being entrepreneurial - finding those moments and recognising their potential. Join us on our journey of building a new kind of organisation to reset expectations of what a bio-pharmaceutical company can be. This means we’re opening new ways to work, pioneering cutting edge methods and bringing unexpected teams together.

Come and join our journey - Apply today!

Where can I find out more?
Our Social Media, Follow AstraZeneca on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/1603/
Follow AstraZeneca on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/astrazenecacareers/
Follow AstraZeneca on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/astrazeneca_careers/?hl=en

Title: Team Lead - Analytics & Data Science
Description:
Why Avaus?
We are the leading marketing and sales transformation partner in the Nordics! We are 120 colleagues located at our offices in Helsinki, Stockholm, Munich, Milan and Gdansk. As a company, we have more than 15 years of experience in data-driven marketing and sales in large organizations across B2C & B2B industries.

Our vision is to become the leading actionable marketing data-asset provider in Europe by 2025. We believe that to survive, companies need to invest heavily in capabilities related to intelligence & AI, customer experience, personalisation and change management. Our mission is to foster customer-centric organizations equipped to grow and face the future. Our own future growth is heavily driven by activating data and analytics for our clients.

The Team
The Analytics team at Avaus consists of data scientists, BI & CRM analysts, and is a team of highly skilled and ambitious people, eager to improve our clients’ results by providing them with better decisions and actions based on data. We work in a wide range of tools and languages to orchestrate and automate the activation of customer data. We are a social crew and enjoy working closely together and learning from one another.

The role
As the Team Lead for our Analytics team, you will be responsible for managing team development plans, coach and guide team members and assist our operations matching the right person for projects. You will also be responsible for the team's career development, recruitment, resourcing and establishing a culture in line with Avaus cultural cornerstones. As a team lead you will need to be a trusted role model for your team and among your peers. Apart from leading your team, you’re also expected to act as a subject-matter expert in client projects. You will most likely be doing some of these things also:

People & team management
Performance reviews and dito assessments, including salary reviews
Coaching of individuals and teams
Personal & career development plans and execution
Competence area customer delivery and subject matter expertise
Team building
Operations & resourcing
Contribute to sales cases within competence area
1-1:s and individual follow-up
Participate in building a growth mindset and culture within the organization
Thought-leadership around the selected topic, both internally and externally
Who are you?
For this role, we are primarily looking for someone with strong leadership skills. It’s preferable if you have experience within marketing automation, CRM Marketing, Content automation and consulting in general. The role will also include supporting client projects and helping clients define and execute on personalization strategies.

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree within a relevant field
Multiple years of relevant work experience, preferably within consulting
Consultancy mindset and the ability to work in fast paced environments
Proven track record within people and team leadership
Extensive experience in data, analytics and reporting
Fluent in Swedish, as our customers require us to communicate in Swedish
Fluent in English
Practical information
This is a permanent position with a 6 months’ probation period, based at our Stockholm office at Katarinavägen 17. Starting date as soon as possible or by agreement. We offer a hybrid remote workplace and you will report to Head of Delivery.

Already feel like one of us? Send your applications in English as soon as possible, but no later than 2023-02-28. If you have any questions about the position, please contact Paola Banegas, Head of Talant. Due to GDPR, we only accept applications through our career page.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Title: Sustainability and EHS Business Analyst
Description:
Location
Sweden, Fagersta, Sweden
Come join our professional team – delivering top class service and specialist knowledge! To Sandvik Machining Solutions(SMS), hosted in the Division Seco Tools and this new role, we’re now looking for a Sustainability and EHS Business Analyst. Take the chance to be part of our exciting world!
A genuine interest in our customers’ success, our family spirit and personal commitment are the values that summarize our corporate culture. These values reflect a shared view of the business and unite Seco’s employees across both geographical and cultural borders. EHS and sustainability are our main priorities, and we actively and consciously work to create a culture where safety always comes first – regardless of the circumstances.
About the job
In this position, you provide proactive decision support and recommendations by developing and analyzing EHS and Sustainability data and performance indicators. You also perform the required reporting of EHS and Sustainability data according to internal and external requirements. In this role, you work closely to the chair of SMS Sustainability & EHS Council.
Also included in your job:
Design efficient and relevant reporting structures and tools for Sustainability and EHS at SMS.
Responsible to consolidate data from various sources and create required analysis and reports.
Collaborate with stakeholders and be proactive in building subject expertise and awareness of future demands on company sustainability reporting. Coordinate work within SMS to gather needed data for required Sustainability and EHS reporting.
Proactively perform data analysis to inform about development and support decision making, as well as external trend reporting.
Administration and arrangement connected to SMS Sustainability & EHS Council.
The location for this position is in Fagersta, Sweden, or flexible within central Europe. However, we also offer part-time remote work possibilities, and some travel is included in your job.
Your profile
We’re looking for someone with a university degree in business administration or data science. You have a background from working in a similar role in industrial manufacturing in a global setting – for example process development, management, development of procedures or definitions.
We also appreciate your:
Experience from working with process development/management, developing procedures and definitions.
Knowledge in various sustainability requirements.
Awareness of auditing and internal control procedures.
Knowledge in software solutions and a sense for technical opportunities.
Microsoft 360 solutions experience, especially for Power BI and Excel.
Subject matter expertise and awareness of future demands on company sustainability reporting.
Awareness of Sustainability Reporting Frameworks and internationally accepted frameworks for disclosing climate related information.
Excellent English skills, both in written and verbal.
Your personality contributes to our success! This position requires analytical and problem-solving skills, and your thorough approach allows you to both keep an overall view while paying close attention details. You’re result-oriented and have the ability to identify solutions – taking great pride in delivering high quality in a timely manner.
Our Seco culture

Title: Commercial Marketing Automation Specialist
Description:
Commercial Marketing Automation Specialist
THE OPPORTUNITY
Are you a commercially driven marketing automation specialist with at least two years of work experience and relevant coding knowledge in Salesforce Marketing Cloud? Do you have a proven track record of delivering successful marketing campaigns and driving revenue growth for your clients? If so, we want to hear from you!
We are looking for a dynamic and driven individual to join our team as a Commercial Marketing Automation Specialist. In this role, you will be a key player in designing, implementing, and managing automated marketing campaigns within Salesforce Marketing Cloud.
As a Commercial Marketing Automation Specialist, you will have a deep understanding of marketing automation best practices, and be able to create and execute effective development that drives results. You will also have experience working with large data sets, and be comfortable using data to inform your decisions and optimize your campaigns.
In addition to your technical skills, you will also have strong communication and project management abilities. You will be able to work collaboratively with other team members and be comfortable presenting your work to other departments and senior management.
If you are a commercially minded marketing automation specialist with at least two years of work experience and relevant coding knowledge in Salesforce Marketing Cloud, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity. This is a fantastic opportunity to join a growing team and take your career to the next level.
WHAT YOU WILL DO
Evaluate and create solutions based on requirements and customer needs
Close collaboration with developers and data scientists from IT department
Configure and manage data flows to Salesforce Marketing Cloud
Create and maintain dynamic and personalized content blocks for emails
Create and maintain project documentation
Bridge business needs with tech
Help out with bugs connected to data, integrations, and logic in emails
YOUR PROFILE
To be successful in this role you have a deep understanding of marketing automation best practices. You are commercially driven and love combining tech with business needs. You have an analytical mindset and your approach is solution-oriented and proactive.
Background in Informatics, Engineering, IT, Marketing Automation, and/or Marketing
Experience with development in Salesforce Marketing Cloud or any other CRM and Marketing Automation tool like Braze, Hubspot, Pardot
Experience creating and executing successful campaigns
Experience with scrum methodology and associated tools (Confluence, Jira, etc)
Relevant qualifications in coding languages such as HTML, CSS, and SQL
Strong communication and project management abilities
Fluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered)
_
Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process._
*
We look forward to your application!*
BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor
A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania, and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?
We are an equal-opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Experienced Scientist in Solid State and Formulations Modelling
Description:
Do you have expertise in and passion for deriving knowledge from data and modelling? Would you like to apply your expertise to implement molecular dynamics simulations on drug formulations such as amorphous solid dispersions or formulated peptides? Then join is in this great opportunity!
AstraZeneca is a global, science-driven biopharmaceutical business and our innovative medicines are used by millions of patients worldwide. Ultimately, our aim is to work towards a cure for some of the world’s most complex diseases. Whether that’s by shaping the patient ecosystem and focusing on outcomes, or by progressing potential medicines and accelerating their launch.
Pharmaceutical Sciences at AstraZeneca delivers the therapies of the future through scientific leadership in drug delivery, design of synthetic routes, and manufacturing of Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients and drug products. In essence, we are working “from molecule to medicine” to develop medicines for our patients today and tomorrow.
The Data Science and Modelling department within Pharmaceutical Sciences is developing a digital transformation strategy to drive innovation, optimization of the drug development process and data-driven decision making.
We now have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Scientist or Associate Principal Scientist, depending on your background and experience, in our Product modelling team. You may be based either in Gothenburg, Sweden or Macclesfield, UK.
What you'll do
In this role you will get the opportunity to engage with key internal and external key collaborators to identify and validate impactful solutions to provide scientific leadership and drive innovation. You will simply be at the forefront of the digital transformation within AstraZeneca, turning ideas into life changing medicines for patients!
You will be part of the digital transformation and use predictions in close collaboration with experimentalists to make solid-state risk assessments and impact on drug projects.
Typical responsibilities in this role
Use molecular modelling to design and understand formulated drug products and delivery systems. This may cover amorphous systems, amorphous solid dispersions, formulated peptides, or lipid nanoparticles.
In drug development projects, be responsible for leading solid-state and materials simulations for solid state risk assessments
Develop and implement proof-of-concept models and workflows to be used by other scientists
Explore new modelling approaches to address the complex interplay between pharmaceutical ingredients in a formulated product.
Publish your novel science.
Essential requirements
PhD in computational chemistry, physics, or equivalent
Track record of applying molecular modelling to druglike molecules
Proven experience of molecular dynamics simulations of biomolecular systems, e.g. formulations
Skills and experience in solid-state and materials modelling, such as periodic calculations employing DFT
Good chemistry and solid-state knowledge. Knowledge of end-to-end software such as Gromacs, VASP, Materials Studio, CCDC suite, Schrödinger package or equivalent is beneficial. Good knowledge of Python programming, and scripting.
Excellent communication skills, written and spoken
Self-motivated
Team player
Why AstraZeneca
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
So, what’s next?
