Title: Methodology for scenario modeling from raw sensor data for autonomous drive odd
Description:
CEVT is here to make urban mobility enjoyable, smart and sustainable. We fast-track innovation and transform ideas into pioneering technology solutions. Automotive is in our DNA and intelligent mobility is our core. We serve society with sustainable mobility solutions, both private and shared. As part of ZEEKR and the Geely family, one of the most innovative and fastest growing global mobility groups, our work comes to life in products and services from world-leading brands. CEVT was built by people from all over the world. We’re flexible, fast, and always in motion.
Master Thesis Project - Methodology for scenario modeling from raw sensor data for autonomous drive odd
Background
As a Master Thesis Student hosted in China Euro Vehicle Technology, you will be working on a specific and valuable applied research problem in the field of Autonomous Drive. You will work among a diverse team with different expertise and carry out your research with the support from our experts and engineers within AD, simulation, developers, designers, and professionals.
You will also be able to work with large-and-diversified data owned by CEVT. Your research outcome will help improve both in AD team at CEVT and your personal skills.
Scope
Data is a fundamental part of developing a highly automated vehicle. CEVT as one of the biggest and at the same time youngest OEMs in the industry, is planning for deploying its AD level 4 vehicles into the market. To that end CEVT has collected its own sensor/vehicle data which are stored locally at its premises.
The next step for us at AD team is to get our hands on the real-world data and analyse it for a better understanding of operation design domain of our vehicles, prior to the deployment of them on the public roads for validation and verification. Although CEVT has close collaborations with many of the top players in the industry, we at AD team would like to amplify the in-house knowledge of our own data. Furthermore, having synergy with CEVT’s mission and vision is one our priorities within the team.
The main idea of this thesis, having the sensor/vehicle data, is to support AD team to formulate the big data into meaningful categories using machine learning algorithms and AI. While there is no one single solution to aggregate that, the key is to come up with the most suitable and efficient method to find patterns or categories in the big data. The result of this thesis project can be used as an input to the more advanced analytical tools, such as scenario extraction tool and simulation tools. Therefore, it is important to find a solution which is extensible for other datasets, such as other sensors’ data or even synthetic data. In another word, it potentially prepares the fundamentals for future work within AD or even in a bigger scope, CEVT.
Project steps
Investigate on the data, including data mining and pre-processing
Find a method to categorize the given data into meaningful scenarios using unsupervised learning
Benchmarking using multiple datasets both inhouse and commercial datasets
Test and validate the developed method using ground truth/reference sensor information
Extended scope: Integrate the method into the SIL environment for ease of scenario extraction
Prerequisites
At least bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering, automotive engineering, data science, computer science, statistics, and mathematics
General knowledge/background in autonomous cars
Master student
Number of students: 1-2, please apply with CV and cover letter.
Starting date: January 2023. The duration of the thesis work is 20 weeks

For more information about the master thesis project please contact:
Yasaman Alavi, System Engineer, +46793393719, yasaman.alavi@cevt.se
Last application date: 2022-10-28
Apply today. We will perform ongoing selection during the application period. We look forward to hearing from you!
Please note that due to GDPR regulations we can only accept applications sent through the recruitment system, not via email or other channels.

Title: Senior data manager
Description:
Nu letar Knowit Helsingborg efter dig som har erfarenhet av Data Science och Data Engineering. Jobbar du med dataanalys och datahantering, och känner dig redo för att bidra med insikter på en ny arbetsplats? Hos oss får du möjligheten att bygga upp ett eget team och driva affären inom Data Science med riktigt härliga kollegor. Vi är redo. Är du?
Om oss
25 november 2021. Det kanske inte är något särskilt med det datumet för dig. Men för oss på Knowit är det en dag som vi alltid kommer minnas. Den dagen startade vi vårt dotterbolag i Helsingborg med Christian Rydström vid rodret. Vi brukar beskriva oss som ett riktigt härligt bolag med start-up känsla, men med Knowits stora trygghet och muskler i ryggen. En perfekt kombination, eller hur?
Vi har idag byggt upp ett team på 14 personer bestående av både utvecklare, projektledare och UX-designers. Vi är schysta, nära, tillgängliga och älskar innovation. Genom en nära dialog med din närmsta chef lovar vi att göra vårt yttersta för att nästa projekt blir ditt livs bästa hittills. Vi värdesätter en kultur med närhet och gemenskap, vi gillar att lyssna när du har förbättringsförslag i projekten, eller nya idéer på event. Vi kommer alltid uppmuntra dig till att testa nya lösningar. Vi överdrev inte när vi sa att vi älskar innovation.
Här välkomnas du av kollegor som André Parnelöv, Kristian Salov och Veronika Liverstam. I dagsläget sitter vi i lokaler på Kungsgatan 6, men i slutet på året bär det av till vårt helt nya, alldeles egna kontor i Oceanhamnen. Vill du ha hunnit bli lite varm i kläderna innan flytten? Fortsätt läs!
Om rollen
Knowit i Helsingborg är ett dotterbolag med starkt tillväxtfokus och härnäst letar vi efter dig som vill bygga upp ett nytt område tillsammans med oss. Rollen kommer dels innebära debiterande uppdrag inom Data Science, dels att bygga upp ditt team inom området. Detta tror vi att du kommer göra genom ett redan befintligt kontaktnät, men givetvis också med hjälp av dina kollegor. Med andra ord kommer du få stor möjlighet att växa och utvecklas i din roll.
Om dig
Vi tror att du har jobbat med data science och data engineering de senaste åren, och känner dig redo för nästa steg. Du har förmodligen jobbat inom områden som AI och Machine Learning. Vidare har du förståelse för databaser, vikten av och hur man jobbar med integrationer samt har erfarenhet av relevanta verktyg (till exempel Qlik eller Power BI).
Vi ser det som väldigt meriterande om du har god förståelse för hur moderna molnplattformar och tjänster möjliggör processering av data från källsystem till färdig dataprodukt. Har du även jobbat med automatisering och datapipelines är det positivt.
Vi ser gärna att du har förståelse för rollen som konsult, och tycker det verkar spännande att vara med och bygga upp ett nytt område i Knowit Helsingborg. Har du erfarenhet av att driva projekt och affärer sedan tidigare ser vi det som starkt meriterande. I denna rollen ser vi gärna att du behärskar både svenska och engelska i tal och skrift.
Frågor? We're more than happy to answer them
Kontakta rekryterare Elin Zahlander på elin.zahlander@knowit.se eller 0736-56 35 75 alternativt VD Christian Rydström på christian.rydstrom@knowit.se eller 0703-41 40 81.
Ansökan
Vi använder analyser i rekryteringsprocessen för att säkerställa en rättvis bedömning av dig som kandidat och ha ett kompetensbaserat urval. Vi arbetar med löpande urval, så varmt välkommen att söka tjänsten redan idag!

Friends of Knowit
Var det här jobbet inte riktigt din kopp te? Eller kanske inte tedags just nu bara? Häng då på i Friends of Knowit istället för att få info om nyheter och aktuella events hos oss – no strings attached – bara enkel vänskap!

Title: Azure Data Engineer - Malmö
Description:
As an Azure Data Engineer you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards data-driven decision-making. We are all passionate about data!
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are partners with different providers of technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Azure Data Factory
Experience in Data Lake or Lakehouse Architecture
Excellent SQL syntax skills
Information- and Data Warehouse modeling
Good skills in code versioning such as GIT GitHub, DevOps
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience from platform modernization
Experience from Tabular cubes and DAX
Databricks
Snowflake
Experience in Snowpro, Matillion or DBT
Data vault modeling
Agile work process

Title: Software Engineer - Advanced Analytics and AI
Description:
Let's create change together.
Nothing beats being part of positive change. We’re on a truly exciting journey, working together in a fast-paced global environment to break new ground in almost every aspect of our operations. Right now, we have an exciting job opening for you in Information Technology/Digital

What's in it for you
The Advanced Analytics & AI (AA&AI) organization is tasked with identifying opportunities for the application of data science, artificial intelligence, and machine learning throughout the company, and then acting on those opportunities. In addition, we develop and operate tools and processes to accelerate and support all teams using data science and machine learning at Volvo Cars.

We are now looking for software engineers to join our teams in Gothenburg. Two teams within AA&AI are recruiting: the Machine Learning Engineering and Operations team and the Data Science team. Your background and interests will determine where you would fit best - the requirements for the roles are very similar.

These roles do not require machine learning expertise and are ideal for talented and experienced software engineers that want to enter the field of applied AI.

You and your skills
You have several years of professional software development experience. You are a self-starter and ready to take the lead on challenging problems. You have excellent communication skills and are eager to share knowledge with your peers. You speak Python almost as well as your native language. Code quality and unit testing are second nature to you, and you know how to design reusable code. You are curious about new tech, and you're excited to step out of your comfort zone and acquire new skills.


What you’ll do
You will work in a virtual team consisting of data scientists, ML engineers, MLOps engineers, and product managers. You will have a big influence over the development process of the services and ML models. This means that you will develop new features and refactor existing ones where it's needed. You will also guide and educate your peers through code reviews and give suggestions on design patterns. Depending on your interests, you will also contribute to the data science platform which is used by dozens of teams across the organization. This might entail the development and deployment of microservices, evolving existing cloud-native automation, and contributing to the open-source projects that we use in our tech stack.

How to learn more and apply
For questions about the position please contact Ronnie Jansson at ronnie.jansson@volvocars.com. For questions regarding the recruitment process, please contact Senior Tech Recruiter, Noopur Thatte at noopur.thatte@volvocars.com. Please note that applications via email will not be accepted.

'This job is eligible for a referral bonus.'

Who are we?
Everything we do starts with people. Our purpose is to provide freedom to move, in a personal, sustainable and safe way. We are committed to simplifying our customers’ lives by offering better technology solutions that improve their impact on the world and bringing the most advanced mobility innovations to protect them, their loved ones and the people around them.


Volvo Cars’ continued success is the result of a collaborative, diverse, and inclusive working environment. The people of Volvo Cars are committed to making a difference in our world. Today, we are one of the most well-known and respected car brands, with over 40,000 employees across the globe. We believe in bringing out the best in each other and harnessing the true power of people. At Volvo Cars your career is designed around your talents and aspirations so you can reach your full potential. Join us on a journey of a lifetime as we create safety, autonomous driving and electrification technologies of tomorrow.

Title: Data Science Lead till SJ
Description:
I den här rollen är du ansvarig för att samla och utveckla SJ-koncernens Data Scientists genom att både själv driva djupgående initiativ liksom att organisera och stötta data science-arbetet tvärs koncernen. Organisatoriskt tillhör du SJ-koncernens centrala avdelning för Data & Analys och rapporterar till chefen för Data & Analys.
Följ med på vår resa mot ett hållbart samhälle! SJ - Framtidens sätt att resa.
SJ är på en resa. En resa där målet är att bidra till ett hållbart samhälle genom att möjliggöra klimatsmart resande, i Sverige och i Norden. Vägen dit kantas av en mängd spännande möjligheter och utmaningar de kommande åren.
Vi växer och utvecklas inom hela verksamheten. Mångmiljardinvesteringar i nya moderna tåg, investeringar i digitala system för att effektivisera vår verksamhet, kompetensutveckling av vår personal, listan kan göras lång. Allt detta görs med kunden i fokus och med målet att göra det möjligt för fler att göra det hållbara resevalet.
Till huvudkontoret på Vasagatan 10 i Stockholm, söker vi nu en Data Science Lead som en grundläggande del i att etablera SJs Data & Analys-avdelning och genom det bidra till vår långsiktiga framgång.
Arbetet sker dels i nära samarbete med närmsta gruppen, dels med övriga på SJ som arbetar med avancerad/operationaliserad analys. Rollen är en av de första pusselbitarna som läggs för att skapa grunden till ett mer datadrivet SJ och avdelningen Data & Analys har som uppdrag att driva och guida koncernen framåt på den resan. Vi söker därför en driven och erfaren Data Scientist som kan leda i arbetet att låsa upp den outnyttjade potential som finns i våra omfattande datatillgångar.
Vem söker vi?
Vi söker dig med gedigen erfarenhet av avancerad/operationaliserad analys i komplexa och storskaliga miljöer tillsammans med god förmåga och intresse för att leda andra i en virtuell organisation. I botten har du akademisk examen inom matematiktung inriktning, exempelvis ingenjörsutbildning med fokus på matematik, statistik, datavetenskap, data science eller motsvarande. Du har erfarenhet av olika tekniska plattformar och programmeringsspråk och är väl insatt i hur samverkan med systemutvecklare, data engineers och kravställare kan och bör ske i en agil omgivning. Antagligen har du erfarenhet från en mogen kontext sett till förmåga att utvinna värde från data men har ett intresse för att själv vara med och bygga upp något liknande från grunden.
Du är självgående, nyfiken och ansvarstagande samt får energi av att växla mellan mer övergripande strukturella uppgifter och de som kräver en mer handfast och detaljerad insats.
Arbetsbeskrivning
Som Data Science Lead ansvarar du för att etablera, driva och utveckla samarbete i tvärfunktionellt community med de inom SJ som arbetar med data science-relaterade frågor. I detta ingår till en början att samla gruppen och fokusera dess medlemmar till gemensamma arbetssätt och verktyg för att sen tillsammans utforska nya möjligheter. Arbetet innebär även att bidra till den strategiska planen för hur SJs förmåga kopplat till data science ska utvecklas.
Arbetet bygger alltså på kontinuerlig dialog med koncernens alla delar och att identifiera och samla in utvecklingsbehov för att sedan prioritera dessa för genomförande. Du kommer att stödja andra och även driva egna utvecklingsinitiativ, vissa från grunden och andra genom att vidareutveckla och underhålla sedan tidigare framtagna lösningar.
Ambitionen är att på sikt utöka avdelningen Data & Analys med ytterligare Data Scientist-förmåga vilket då kommer innebära att uppgiften som Data Science Lead växer i form av ett arbetsledningsansvar.
Vad kan SJ erbjuda dig?
På SJ ger vi dig goda möjligheter och utrymme att påverka och bidra till utveckling. Det här är en utmanande och intressant roll som erbjuder frihet i kombination med stort ansvar. En roll som bidrar till, och möjliggör, ett hållbart resande. SJs utveckling och tillväxt har varit och förväntas långsiktigt att vara mycket god. Vår flexibilitet och förmåga att anpassa verksamheten till verkligheten har utvecklats till en av bolagets styrkor.
Kontakt
I den här rekryteringen samarbetar SJ med Jefferson Wells. För mer information om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Malin Magnusson 076-780 68 64.
Vi ser gärna att du skickar in din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast 15 feb.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
SJ vet att mångfald ger fler perspektiv och ökar SJs konkurrenskraft. Vi välkomnar därför sökanden med olika bakgrunder som vill vara med och bidra till ett inkluderande arbetsklimat.
SJ för människor närmare varandra, varje dag.
SJ är ett svenskt reseföretag som erbjuder hållbara tågresor i egen regi och i samarbete med andra. SJ är ett av Sveriges grönaste varumärken och en del av lösningen för att klimatmålen ska nås. Koncernens 5400 medarbetare i Sverige och Norge bidrar alla till ökat tågresande - framtidens sätt att resa.
Som marknadsledande tågoperatör knyter SJ ihop Sverige, Norge, liksom Skandinaviens huvudstäder och varje dag möts våra kunder och medarbetare på någon av våra 1500 avgångar från över 400 stationer. SJ ägs av svenska staten och har som uppdrag att driva lönsam persontrafik på järnväg.

I den här rollen är du ansvarig för att samla och utveckla SJ-koncernens Data Scientists genom att både själv driva djupgående initiativ liksom att organisera och stötta data science-arbetet tvärs koncernen. Organisatoriskt tillhör du SJ-koncernens centrala avdelning för Data & Analys och rapporterar till chefen för Data & Analys.

Title: Forward-deployed Lead Data Engineer
Description:
Who We Are

Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we work closely with clients to embrace a transformational approach aimed at benefiting all stakeholders—empowering organizations to grow, build sustainable competitive advantage, and drive positive societal impact.

Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives that question the status quo and spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting, technology and design, and corporate and digital ventures. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, fueled by the goal of helping our clients thrive and enabling them to make the world a better place.

Practice Area Profile

BCG GAMMA combines innovative skills in computer science, artificial intelligence (AI), statistics, and machine learning with deep industry and functional expertise. The BCG GAMMA team is comprised of world-class data scientists, software and data engineers, as well as product experts with a consulting mindset.
We specialize in creating competitive advantage for our clients through AI driven transformations. Our teams own the full analytics value-chain end to end: framing new business challenges, designing innovative algorithms, implementing and deploying scalable solutions, and enabling colleagues and clients to fully embrace AI. Our product offerings span from fully custom-build to industry specific leading edge AI software solutions.

What You'll Do

As a forward-deployed Lead Data Engineer, you’ll be part of our rapidly growing engineering team and help build the next generation of AI solutions. You’ll have the chance to partner with clients in a variety of BCG regions and industries, and on key topics like climate change, enabling them to design, build, and deploy new and innovative solutions. Additional responsibilities will include developing and delivering thought leadership in scientific communities and papers as well as leading conferences on behalf of BCG GAMMA.
WHO YOU ARE
We are looking for talented individuals with a passion for data engineering, software development and transforming organizations into AI led innovative companies
Apply data engineering practices and standards to develop robust and maintainable solutions
Actively involved in every part of the software development life cycle
Experienced at guiding non-technical teams and consultants in best practices for large-scale data engineering
Motivated by a fast-paced, service-oriented environment and interacting directly with clients on new features for future product releases
Enjoy collaborating in teams to share software design and solution ideas
A natural problem-solver and intellectually curious across a breadth of industries and topics



What You'll Bring (Experience & Qualifications)

REQUIREMENTS
Masters degree or PhD in computer science (or in a highly related area)
8+ years of relevant industry experience
Previous consulting experience and/or strong leadership positions
Experience in data engineering and working with global and remote agile squads
Proficiency with analytic software programming ideally in python, C++, or SCALA
Fluency with the storage, manipulation, and management of relational, non-relational and streaming data structures, specifically SQL, Spark, and Hadoop
Proficiency with infrastructure as code principles
Experience working on AWS, Azure, or Google cloud infrastructure
NICE TO HAVE
DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD, Terraform
Understanding of parallel computing
Full stack development: GraphQL, React, JavaScript, TypeScript
Data Science and machine learning (Pandas, Scikit learn)
WORK ENVIRONMENT
Fluency in English is required as well as fluency in the local language for most locations
Ability to travel based on client and business needs. Expect 30-50%

Title: Analytics Engineer
Description:
We are looking for an Analytics Engineer to take a crucial part in our data journey. We are developing our data platform with Snowflake and dbt in the center of all our data products. We hope you are as excited as us about developing data products in dbt and on Snowflake. You will work in a remote team of data engineers, DataOps engineers, & BI developers.


In this role, you will be responsible for growing, maintaining and optimizing the core dbt layer for our data products that are business-critical for Qliro. Our mission is to build a company-wide data platform using Snowflake, dbt and Airflow.
Our stack:
Snowflake, dbt, Airflow, Docker, AWS & New Relic
About the role:
As a Analytics Engineer you will be working in the data team and collaborate with data engineers and own the transformation that is the foundation for BI, Analytics and Data Science. Our data products support both internal functions like Finance, Product & Credit but also customer-facing data products like Notifications and Credit decisions.
You will be building data transformation in dbt with close collaboration to both functional analysts and with input from business owners. Our data pipelines are crucial for us as a Business and you will be building, maintaining and supporting both internal and external data products in this role.
We believe you have:
dbt experience
Snowflake experience
GIT experience
Python experience
We believe you are
Passionate about solving complex business problems and building awesome data products with high quality and high velocity. You are someone who continuously seeks improvements, enjoys learning new tools and techniques and having fun together as a data team.
You are logical and analytical minded and are able to communicate technical content to end users. Have a great track record of bringing value to the business by using data, preferably within financial and/or related industries.
Proficient in verbal and written English and enjoys working in a remote team.
WOW in everything we do
Qliro offers a dynamic and fast-paced Fintech environment with teams of driven and flexible individuals. We thrive on challenges and personal growth. Together, we will ensure we continue to create WOW in everything we do.

Title: Data Engineer till Marginalen Bank!
Description:
Motiveras du av att driva transformering där molnresan står i fokus? Trivs du som bäst när du får arbeta med både tekniska lösningar och arkitekturella strategier? Då ser vi gärna att du läser vidare…

Som Data Engineer har du en nyckelroll i bankens resa mot en mer datadriven organisation. Du är en del av Data Automation-teamet inom vår centrala Data & Analytics organisation, där även Data Science och Modellering & Analys-teamen ingår.

Det här är rollen för dig som vill kombinera erfarenhet av hands-on utveckling med arkitektur och strategi.
Rollen är baserad på huvudkontoret i Stockholm men möjlighet till visst arbete hemifrån finns.
Ett urval av dina kommande arbetsuppgifter…

Som Data Engineer arbetar du i ett av våra scrum team inom Data Automation teamet men även med andra funktioner med bankens datastrategi. I rollen arbetar du tillsammans med teamet för att skapa strategier och förutsättningar för Marginalen Banks förflyttning till molnet och möjliggörandet av datadrivna beslut, processer, rapportering och ökad affärsintelligens inom hela banken. Teamet består även av konsulter från andra länder än Sverige. Därav är det ett krav att kunna föra sig i tal och skrift på engelska.
Vem du är…
För att lyckas i rollen ser vi att du har erfarenhet av automatisering, versionshantering och DevOps. Du bör även ha erfarenhet av Azure och några av dess komponenter, exempelvis: Azure Data Factory och Azure Data Lake. Även erfarenhet av Snowflake och GIT är meriterande. Du kanske även har ett intresse och/eller erfarenhet av datamodellering (Data Vault, Kimball, Inmon).
Du är van att arbeta agilt och din nyfikenhet och intresse gör att du ständigt håller dig uppdaterad inom ditt område och på nya tekniker. Du ser lösningar framför hinder och brinner för att kombinera dina tekniska kunskaper med att driva och att påverka. Du trivs att jobba i team, är prestigelös och delar kunskap och hjälper andra på ett ödmjukt sätt.
Vad Marginalen Bank erbjuder dig…
Hos oss blir du en del av en prestigelös organisation där du förutsätts delta aktivt samt påverka processer och rutiner. Vi arbetar agilt och skapar effektiva lösningar och fattar goda och genomtänkta beslut. Vi är innovativa, har hög moral, tänker och agerar hållbart, arbetar proaktivt och driver igenom fattade beslut med en handlingskraft och i tid.
Vårt huvudkontor, mitt i centrala Stockholm, huserar i byggnaden Grönlandet - ett arkitektoniskt mästerverk signerat Sigurd Lewerentz från 1932. Vi har en egen restaurang som lagar ekologisk mat vilket är en extra lyx i vår vardag! Här får du arbeta med medarbetare som känner stolthet, arbetsglädje och delaktighet. Vi erbjuder också personlig utveckling ,volontärdag, tjänstepension, friskvårdsbidrag och hälsoförsäkring vilket bara är några av alla våra förmåner. - Läs gärna mer om vår kultur, våra värdeord och våra förmåner på vår hemsida.
Låter detta som något för dig, tveka då inte att kontakta oss!
Vid eventuella frågor är du välkommen att kontakta rekryterande ledare Jonathan Söderström på Jonathan.Soderstrom@Marginalen.se. Då urvalsprocessen sker löpande är du varmt välkommen med din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast den 15-03-2023.

Title: Solution Architect – Data & AI
Description:
As a Solution Architect, you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers make the right decisions and give them a solid foundation to succeed on their journey.
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data has a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
We are partners with different technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of clients and technologies, together with amazing colleagues.
As a Solution Architect, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing optimal technical solutions.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients in the decision making of which platform and architecture to use
Integration of different data sources, modeling and loading of data
Optimizing different solutions (data warehouse, data lakehouse, machine learning) depending on the purpose
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
Who We Are
Capgemini, Insights & Data, is the Nordic benchmark in Data, Analytics and AI. We number more than 300 consultants, distributed across our offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the market’s renowned experts work with us, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards data-driven decisions. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global roll outs, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
What we are looking for:
Experience in architecting and designing data solutions using trade-off analysis
Knowledge of different information architecture patterns (e.g. dimensional model, data vault 2.0, data mesh, lakehouse)
Experience in DevOps tools including version control (Git), CI/CD pipelines and infrastructure as code (Terraform)
Experience in architecture governance and architecture documentation
Familiar with data management, data security, and access control in the cloud
Prototyping mindset and familiar with Python, Pyspark and SQL
Experience working with streaming data
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills.
What we see as qualifying:
Hands on experience in setting up cloud architecture in Azure, AWS or GCP
Cloud architect certification or Databricks certification
Evidence of architectural trade off analysis
Hands on experience for designing data ingestion and transformation patterns in the cloud
DataOps solution design experience (observability, error handling)
Experience designing storage topologies, data models and optionally understanding of domain driven design
Experience working with cloud storage, cloud data pipeline tools, CDC tools and data catalogues
Stakeholder management

Title: Volvo GTT Graduate Program 2023 - Data Science Quality & CS
Description:
Sweden
Position Description
Work with the latest technologies to shape tomorrow's society

Imagine yourself working with some of the sharpest and most creative brains in the transport and infrastructure industry, developing cutting-edge technologies and sustainable transport solutions that will change the future of society. We are passionate about what we do, we aim for high performance and thrive on teamwork. We are almost 100,000 colleagues united around the world by a culture of care, empowerment, and inclusiveness, where each one of us can give our very best. Every day, we collaborate with partners and experts in our field to leave our company and society in a better shape for the next generation.

The Engineering Graduate program

The Engineering Graduate Program at Volvo Group Trucks Technology is a global 12-month program where you are offered the perfect mix of on-the-job learning and diverse training modules. You will get not only the chance to use your technical and creative engineering skills, but also improving your soft skills while gaining valuable experience working with real products on real business challenges.

You will have the opportunity to travel across the globe, exploring different sites, markets and working with people from several nationalities. Besides your manager, who will guide and support you in your daily job, you will have a supportive network of peer graduates, colleagues across the globe and senior leaders to help you excel. We hope you will learn as much from us as we will from you.

How you will make an impact

At Volvo GTT, we have the ambitions to elevate the usage of data and analytics to a more advanced level in our decision-making processes. Hereby, we strive to create more values for our customers by developing more efficient, sustainable, and safe products and solutions.

To achieve that, we are looking for an ambitious candidate who is willing to become a technical leader in our organization and impact the future of the company by levering the analytical skills, data driven insights and innovative thinking. The candidate should be able to understand the domain knowledge and the ultimate need of our partners. Though innovative thinking, analytics, and programming skills you will need to provide to the partners state-of-the-art solutions that creates value to the company and the end customer.

Who are you?

We are looking for the next generation engineers who wants to make a real difference to society. You are passionate about what you do, have a curious mind and are willing to learn. Just like us, you thrive on teamwork.

In order to qualify for the Engineering Graduate program you must have completed a master’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering Physics, Software Engineering, Mathematics, Statistics, Physics or similar prior to the start of the program but not more than 18 months ago. You should not have more than two years full-time working experience prior to starting. You also need to be fluent in English, both written and verbal.

What’s in it for me?

Our Engineering Graduate Program starts in August 2023, and you will be offered a permanent position at Volvo Group Trucks Technology with placement in Sweden, Gothenburg. These are some of the benefits of joining our program:
An opportunity to work with the latest technology
An exciting and global working environment with experienced colleagues
Possibility to gain international experience through a short-term assignment abroad
A competitive salary and permanent position from day one
A variety of workshops and seminars designed to help you grow into your future career at Volvo Group
Possibility to shape your own career with endless career opportunities

About Volvo Group Trucks Technology

Volvo Group Trucks Technology is the global research and development organization of the Volvo Group. We provide state-of-the-art research, engineering, product planning and project execution to final delivery and support of todays and tomorrow’s transport and infrastructure solutions.

The application process
The journey begins! An email confirmation will be sent as soon as you submit your application. After this, it is still possible to update your personal profile by login into your account. The hiring team will review your application together with the hiring manager. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted with information about the following steps.

If you have any questions, please contact:
Info.Engineering.Graduate.Program@volvo.com

Kindly note that due to GDPR, we will not accept applications via mail. Please use our career site.

About us
The Volvo Group drives prosperity through transport solutions, offering trucks, buses, construction equipment, power solutions for marine and industrial applications, financing and services that increase our customers’ uptime and productivity. Founded in 1927, the Volvo Group is committed to shaping the future landscape of sustainable transport and infrastructure solutions. Countless career opportunities are offered across the group’s leading brands and entities that share a culture of Trust, Passion, High Performance, Change and Customer Success.
www.volvogroup.com/career.
Volvo Group Trucks Technology provides Volvo Group Trucks and Business Area's with state-of-the-art research, cutting-edge engineering, product planning and purchasing services, as well as aftermarket product support. With Volvo Group Trucks Technology you will be part of a global and diverse team of highly skilled professionals who work with passion, trust each other and embrace change to stay ahead. We make our customers win.

Regular
