Title: Manager within Data & Analytics
Description:
BearingPoint’s Data & Analytics team combine broad business understanding with deep technology expertise to help our clients make insight driven decisions on all levels of their organization. We help our clients explore the full potential of their data using modern tools and technologies. To meet current and future clients’ needs we are looking to strengthen our team with a Manager with a passion for both business and technology who will be responsible for delivering projects and developing our business within Data & Analytics. The position is based in Stockholm.
We would like to see following in our new colleagues’ profile:
Passion for technology and transforming data to business value
6+ years in consulting delivering projects and developing business
Significant hands on experience with advanced analytics, business intelligence, and/or data warehousing
Experience with advising clients on topics related to data strategy, data governance, and/or building Data & Analytics teams
Experience with SQL, Python, or similar tools in a Data & Analytics context
Master’s degree with excellent academic record
Excellent communication skills both written and spoken
Fluency in Swedish and English (both written and spoken)
Ability to travel if necessary
Our new colleague can expect following from us:
A unique opportunity to carry out challenging Data & Analytics projects including both strategic advisory and business-oriented data science
Exciting career opportunities and possibilities to learn and grow as fast as you desire
Highly competent and down-to-earth colleagues
An informal and “Easy to work with” culture
Competitive compensation and benefits
If this sounds interesting, then we would be happy to receive an application (CV and personal letter) from you. The selection and interview process are ongoing, so we would appreciate your application at your earliest convenience.
About BearingPoint
BearingPoint is an independent management and technology consultancy firm with European roots and a global reach. The company operates in three units: Consulting, Solutions and Ventures. Consulting covers the advisory business; Solutions provides the tools for successful digital transformation, regulatory technology and advanced analytics; Ventures drives the financing and development of start-ups. BearingPoint’s clients include many of the world’s leading companies and organizations. The firm has a global consulting network with more than 10,000 people and supports clients in over 75 countries, engaging with them to achieve measurable and sustainable success.

Title: Research Analyst
Description:
AMEXCI AB is an Additive Manufacturing company founded by twelve industrial companies in Sweden. Our vision is to futureproof our Nordic Industries together with our customers, by accelerating the industrial adoption of Additive Manufacturing (AM/Industrial 3D printing) technologies, making them even more competitive and sustainable on the global market.
We support our customers throughout the entire process chain in the development of their products, using AM as an enabler for higher performance, increased efficiency, shorter lead times, and more. At our labs in Karlskoga, Sweden, we have the capability to design, produce and qualify components using state-of-the-art industrial AM equipment.
We are expanding our Research team and we are looking for a strong candidate to join our team as a Research Analyst.

What we offer:
A dynamic and fast paced environment with possibilities of growing within the company
Becoming a part of our team of diverse and talented people from around the world
The possibility of working with one of the fastest growing and impactful technologies of our time
The possibility to collaborate with world leading companies from a diverse range of industries and to contribute to the global advancement of the technology

The Job:
You will be part of the Research department and reporting to the Head of Research, while working in close contact with the entire AMEXCI team
You will support the Research department in customer projects and will have a relevant role within them
You will have the responsibility to run and deliver internal projects
You will work closely with the Application Development department in performing tasks for data-related projects using Excel functions

Qualifications:
You hold a Master of science degree in engineering, mathematics, management information systems, applied data science, material science or similar
You have at least 2 years of experience as a researcher, data scientist/analyst, preferably with a background in market research
You have a structured and independent way of working and always thrive to deliver according to time plan while ensuring the best quality
You are motivated and eager to learn continuously
You are good in analytical thinking, analysis of data and are familiar with writing reports
Previous experience in additive manufacturing, programming, mechanical testing, or quality assurance is a plus
Since our official company language is English, it is important that you have excellent English communication skills
How you are as a person is important to fit within our team so part of the recruitment process will include meeting with your future colleagues.

How to apply
To apply, please send your CV and cover letter to recruitment@amexci.com and mark your application “Research Analyst”. Selection of candidates will occur during the recruitment time. We look forward to receiving your application as soon as possible.
For more information about AMEXCI, please visit www.amexci.com

Title: German Speaking Customer Service Agent
Description:
Customer Service Agent - Germany
THE OPPORTUNITY
Do you have an interest in fashion, see solutions rather than problems and always strive to provide service at a top level? Then this opportunity might be the one for you.
Do you also value a dynamic and international work environment, fun and knowledgeable colleagues as well as a lot of internal career opportunities, then apply and get the chance to join our amazing Customer Service Team.
As our new Customer Service Agent you will join a team, where you together will work towards providing world class service to our customers.

WHAT YOU WILL DO
The first part of your journey at Boozt will be to take part in a thorough training program to create the best possible conditions for you to succeed and excel in your new role. Training sessions and development meetings will be held continuously throughout your time at Boozt.
Together with our trainers you will focus on your development and take part in training sessions to tailor your journey as a Boozter.
Provide top class service to our customers with all inquiries coming in via phone, email or chat
Be our expert when it comes to questions ranging from specific product information, to styling tips, stock status, shipping details, payment queries, and campaign errands
You will be the company’s eyes and ears and will be a truly important part of the “from order to delivery chain” to ensure that we reach our goal of building an unrivaled customer experience

YOUR PROFILE
You speak and write fluently in German.
You are also fluent in English since this is our corporate language and it is a part of your daily tasks to support other markets when needed
You enjoy solving problems, exceeding expectations and has a natural ability to connect with people
You see no obstacles in the challenges of offering quick, informative and individual answers and explanations even in stressful times
Previous experience in the service industry is a plus
Good communication skills and a real interest in expressing yourself well, both in speech and writing (tests will be given as part of our recruitment process)
You are proud of being precise and it is natural for you to be considerate in your behavior both internally and externally

OUR OFFER
This is a chance for you to join our vibrant Customer Service Team, an opportunity to grow and develop with one of the leading Nordic E-commerce companies
Full-time temporary employment for an initial 12 months with the possibility for a permanent position (the employment will start with a 6 month probation period)
Working hours for the German teams are 8:00-17:00 and 10:00-19:00 on a rolling schedule.
Your working schedule will be published for you to see four months in advance
You will join a big international team where we support and learn from each other, but the most important of all we have fun while doing so

Note; the first step in this recruitment process is to conduct an assessment that we send to you by email. This is mandatory to continue in the process.

We look forward to your application!

BOOZT PERKS
Great personal and internal career development
A culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility
Flexible work environment
Driven and passionate international colleagues
A generous employee discount
Wellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor

A LITTLE BIT ABOUT US
We are one of the leading e-commerce players in the Nordics. We offer our customers fashion, kids, sports, beauty, and home on Boozt.com and Booztlet.com. You can find our headquarters in Malmö, Sweden, our Boozt Innovation Lab in the heart of Copenhagen, a data science team in Aarhus, Denmark, our two tech offices in Vilnius, Lithuania and in Poznan, Poland, and our fully automated warehouse in Ängelholm (one of the worlds biggest AutoStores). Our Boozt family consists of +1100 employees from more than 38+ nationalities; we believe that our diverse teams help us build an innovative and vibrant workplace. Would you like to join us on our exciting journey?

We are an equal opportunity employer that embraces diversity and inclusiveness.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.
For further information see www.babyshop.com
ABOUT THE POSITION
Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.
WHAT YOU'LL DO
Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE
You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...
Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE
The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.
Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!
Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Factory Simulation Engineer
Description:
Northvolt has an exciting job offer for a Factory Simulation Engineer to join our diverse and passionate Blueprint team in Stockholm.
In joining us you will play an important part from the very start in building one of the first large scale European battery factories. Northvolt will play an important role in the transformation to a carbon free society.
As a Factory Simulation Engineer, you will interact with factory design in the very early phases. Together with the team, you will contribute dimensioning equipment and buffer capacities for an efficient line balancing. Another integral contribution of the simulation engineer is to use 3D-simulation models to ensure the factory layout space is optimally distributed for material flow and automation to meet production volumes.
Main tool is discrete event simulation using multidisciplinary input parameters.
Key responsibilities include but are not limited to:
Verifying and optimizing factory design by using simulation.
Evaluate operating models and overall production capacity.
Using a standardized, modular and reusable approach to simulation modelling.
Support the Northvolt blueprint philosophy on high level, by capturing best practice manufacturing system configurations to meet production demands.
The person we are looking for is strongly goal oriented, curious and eager to learn. You will get the chance to have a real impact on our success story in Sweden (to start with) and see the results of your work. Our organization requires and values great self-discipline and a natural talent to make things happen.
Apply with CV and cover letter or your complete LinkedIn profile.
Full time employment, fixed salary.
Planned starting date is asap.
Skills & Requirements
We believe that you have :
M.Sc. in Engineering, preferably within System Engineering, Production Management/Logistics, or M.Sc. in Applied and Computational Mathematics/Data Science, with a focus on statistics and optimization.
+3 years of professional experience with material flow simulations or digital manufacturing.
Well-developed communication skills to allow frequent contact with different data respondents and continuous alignments with stakeholders.
Industrial experience from previously worked with designing productions systems or material flows.
Experience with Siemens Plant Simulation or other Discrete Event Simulation (DES) tools.
Experience in programming
Lean production
Statistics / data science
Experience with big data
Experience with machine learning is preferred but not required
Experience with 2D/3D CAD tools is preferred but not required
Specific Skills/Abilities
Excellent English written and oral skills
Highly organized and result-driven
Ability to work well with others in a team environment, as well as independently
An eye for detail
Specific Skills/Abilities
Great Place to Work
World leading technique
Top specialists as team peers
International environment
Fast paced & entrepreneurial culture
Warrant program
Wellness grant

Title: Business Intelligence
Description:
Sopra Steria fortsätter att växa och därför söker vi nu fler nya kollegor till Östersundskontoret inom Data & Analytics. Arbetar du med Business Intelligence, BI, Data Warehousing, Data Engineering, Beslutsstöd, Analytics, Data Science eller Machine learning? För oss är inte det viktiga vad du kallar det utan att du brinner för att hjälpa kunder att skapa värde genom digitalisering. Vi erbjuder en av Sveriges bästa arbetsplatser (enligt Great Place to Work) och har av Gartner rankats till topp fem bolag inom digital transformation.
Tillhörande Östersundskontoret finns möjlighet att ha sin arbetsplats i Åre, där vi har en egen studio i delade lokaler. Bor du redan i Åre, eller är på väg att ta steget? Vi vågar lova dig en omväxlande vardag och otroliga kollegor, på en arbetsplats där trivsel är en strategisk prioritering. Här har vi en lokal förankring men med styrkan av global närvaro. Vi tror på Power of Sharing och arbetar ständigt med att dela med oss av våra kunskaper till varandra och till samhället i stort.
Om tjänsten
Här tillhör du det lokala kontoret, men också det nationella Data & Analytics-teamet. Tillsammans har vi gedigen erfarenhet av att hjälpa våra kunder utveckla och underhålla beslutsstödslösningar på högsta nivå. Vi erbjuder möjligheten att kombinera arbete i något av våra många utmanande uppdrag med vidareutbildning och certifieringar inom området. Vi levererar både i projekt och som helhetsåtagande och arbetar helst tillsammans i team. Vi använder våra sammantagna kompetenser och förmågor till att skapa värde åt våra kunder utifrån deras data. På Sopra Steria ger vi dig verktygen och förutsättningarna för att fortsätta växa i din yrkesroll. Det är så vi jobbar.

Vi är partner med flera stora aktörer inom BI-området, till exempel Microsoft, Oracle, Peltarion och Qlik.
Vi tänker oss att tjänsten i första hand är en anställning på vårt fina kontor i Åre/Östersund, men i dessa digitala tider är vi öppna för mer flexibla lösningar. Vi söker även kollegor till våra fina kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg och Malmö!
Vem är du?
Till den här rollen söker vi dig som har flera års erfarenhet av att jobba med modellering, hantering, lagring och presentation av data. Med din erfarenhet vet du vad som krävs och vi gissar att du är van att hantera till exempel SQL Server, Azure, Redshift, Power BI, Qlik, Quicksight eller Tableau.
Är du nyutexad? Missa inte att kolla in vårat accelerateprogram, utsett till Sveriges bästa inom IT! Accelerate-program | Sopra Steria
I övrigt söker vi dig som:
Gillar att jobba med ny teknik.
Delar med dig av kunskap till dina kollegor.
Är nyfiken och vill utvecklas. På riktigt.
Behärskar svenska och engelska väl i både tal och skrift.
Vilka är vi?
Vi är 47 000 kollegor i 30 länder som är experter inom IT och management. Sopra Steria har blivit utsedda till en av Sveriges bästa arbetsplatser, Karriärföretag 2022 och av Gartner som ett topp 5 bolag inom digital transformation. Tillsammans skapar vi förändring på riktigt genom digitalisering för några av världens främsta bolag inom både privat och offentlig sektor.
Ansökan
Nu vill vi gärna höra lite om dig! Ansök enkelt genom att antingen ladda upp ditt CV eller länka direkt till ditt LinkedIn-konto via annonsen på vår hemsida! Om det fortfarande finns något du funderar över är du välkommen att kontakta Sanna Salén, sanna.salen@soprasteria.com.
Vi jobbar löpande med urval och intervjuer, skicka därför gärna in din ansökan så snart som möjligt.
Vi ser fram emot att få höra ifrån dig!

Title: Trainee - Teknikingenjör informationsbehandling
Description:
Om jobbet
Under tolv månader deltar du i ett omfattande traineeprogram som främjar din personliga utveckling, breddar ditt kontaktnät och ger dig kunskap om våra olika verksamheter. Du rustas i förändrings- och projektledning och tillsammans med övriga traineer deltar du i utvecklingsuppdrag utifrån olika case för att lära och påverka. Du förväntas att själv ta initiativ, etablera kontakter och planera en stor del av ditt traineeår. Som exempel kan du välja att göra studiebesök eller kortare praktikperioder inom de verksamheter som intresserar dig. Det erbjuds möjlighet till samverkan med andra myndigheter och externa aktörer i Sverige och internationellt. I arbetet ingår resor, både nationellt och regionalt.
Enheten digital projekthantering arbetar med ämnesområdena BIM, GIS och datasamordning. Ämnesområdena har strukturerad och effektiv informationshantering som gemensam målsättning. För att kunna säkerställa detta mål arbetar enhetens specialister i tvärfunktionella grupper inom Trafikverkets största specialistorganisation.
Arbetet som trainee kommer att innebära:
att identifiera utvecklingsområden för till exempel automatisering av arbetsflöden
att kombinera kunskap inom informationsbehandling, informationshantering och analys av arbetssätt/processer, med praktiskt tillämpning inom väg- och järnvägsprojekt
att jobba med operativa frågor samt att få delta i strategiska arbeten
Arbetsbeskrivningen kommer att justeras baserat på slutkandidatens kompetensprofil i dialog med din närmaste chef.
Jag som blir din chef heter Johan Landin och ser framemot att få lära känna dig och välkomna dig till Trafikverket. Jag brinner för personlig utveckling, både din och min. Det centrala i mitt ledarskap är empati och målfokus. Med mitt engagemang och min humor göra jag jobbet intressant.
Kvalifikationer
För att trivas som trainee behöver du ha ett stort digitaliseringsintresse, förståelse för digital omställning och en vilja att medverka till att skapa innovation. Arbetet innebär många kontakter både inom och utanför Trafikverket och förutsätter att du som person är duktig på att skapa goda relationer, kommunicera och förmedla budskap på ett enkelt sätt anpassat till mottagaren. Du drivs av att arbeta i en föränderlig miljö och jobbar självständigt, ser vad som behöver göras och agerar därefter. Du har en stark egen drivkraft och besitter en mycket god problemlösningsförmåga som gör att du identifierar problem och utvecklar lösningar ur ett helhetsperspektiv.
Vi söker dig som
har master- eller civilingenjörsexamen om minst 300 hp inom väg- och vattenbyggnad, samhällsplanering, infrastruktur eller data science
har dokumenterad utbildning inom projektledning
har mycket goda kunskaper i svenska i tal och skrift
Det är meriterande om du har
dokumenterad utbildning inom dataanalys eller automation eller machine learning
dokumenterad utbildning inom BIM, GIS eller informationshantering
skrivit eller skriver ditt examensarbete inom något av områdena infrastruktur, bygg och fastighet eller informationsbehandling
Din akademiska examen ska ha uttagits under 2021, 2022, alternativt kommer du att ta din examen senast september 2023.
Övrig information
Vi använder främst mail (från mejladress: noreply@heroma.se) för att göra utskick och kallelser. Kolla din inkorg och även skräppost/SPAM regelbundet under denna tid för att vara säker på att du får all information från oss! I denna rekrytering används webbaserade tester som en del i urvalet.
När du ansöker ska du inte bifoga något personligt brev. Istället för att bifoga personligt brev, får du möjlighet i ansökningsformuläret att beskriva varför du är intresserad av den här tjänsten. Detta är en tillsvidaretjänst som inleds med en provanställning på 6 månader. Tillträde till tjänsten är den 1 september 2023.
De första intervjuerna är planerade att hållas den 6-9 mars 2023 via Skype.
#LI-AB2
Ansökan
De frågor som du får besvara när du skickar in din ansökan kommer att ligga till grund för det första urvalet vi gör.
Som sökande till Trafikverket kan du eventuellt behöva gå igenom en säkerhetsprövning. Den innehåller säkerhetsprövningssamtal och registerkontroll innan anställning, om tjänsten är placerad i säkerhetsklass. I vissa fall krävs svenskt medborgarskap för säkerhetsklassade tjänster.
Inom Investering leder vi de flesta av Trafikverkets projekt inom ombyggnation och nyinvesteringar. Vi arbetar med helheten - från planläggning och byggnation till färdig väg eller järnväg. Hela tiden med fokus på smarta lösningar och effektiv projektledning. Hos oss arbetar du med kollegor och olika intressenter, alla med sina kunskaper och erfarenheter, för att skapa hållbara transportlösningar.
På Trafikverket jobbar vi med att göra Sverige närmare. Vi tror på att en förening av olika erfarenheter, bakgrunder och perspektiv är den bästa grunden för att bygga en arbetsplats fri från diskriminering och en miljö där alla trivs och gör sitt bästa. Vi tror på mångfald där den gemensamma nämnaren är pålitlighet, engagemang och mod. För det är så vi bäst representerar vårt samhälle.

Title: Market Development Director, EMEA
Description:
Who we are
Olink Proteomics is a rapidly growing life science company committed to advancing the understanding of human diseases through proteomics. We are dedicated to innovation, quality, rigor and transparency, providing outstanding solutions and support for human protein biomarker discovery.
The vital role of proteins in understanding human biology has been recognized for many decades, but technological limitations severely restricted the comprehensive investigation of the huge number of proteins that could be important in different biological processes and diseases. With Olink, scientists can now simultaneously measure thousands of human proteins using just a few µL of blood sample, with highly specific, thoroughly validated assays that cover a very wide dynamic range (fg/mL to µg/mL).
In a few years, Olink has grown rapidly from a small, Sweden-based company offering assays for a few hundred proteins, to a NASDAQ-listed organization with a strong global presence, a broad portfolio of flexible protein biomarker solutions and library of high quality, thoroughly validated assays that covers ~3000 proteins.
For more information about Olink, please visit www.olink.com
Position Description
We are looking for an energetic, technically savvy, and deeply processed director-level person who knows every bit of Olink internal workings help drive the company’s growth into clinical and custom applications. Particular attention will be needed on the Focus product line and in helping to train up the number new mid-plex Business Development Specialists in not just the technical aspects of the role but in all of nuances cultural and informal working practices.
This role would report to the Regional VP and work in tandem with our Business Development Directors to help drive sales into the region and prepare our path to diagnostic applications.
Primary Responsibilities
Grow overall revenue from mid-plex (Target, Signature, and Focus) service and kit businesses
Learn and establish best practices to help Olink move from the clinical research arena to diagnostics
Under guidance of regional VP and product marketing, develop and build a database of language, practice, and positioning around RUO, IVD, CE, LDT, 510K, Clinical, Diagnostics, and related topics
Learn and teach the possibilities and boundaries of Olink’s applicability in the clinical space with the context of CFR Part 11 compliance, ISO 13485 capabilities, and FDA guidelines
Help teach Business Development Specialists (BDS) how to provide technical presentations to potential clients interested in protein biomarker discovery in the mid-plex space to both research and clinical segments
Teach BDS how to manage existing and new proteomics projects
Become the sales guru around the Focus product
Work in tight coordination with but not overlap traditional Sales Enablement
Provide study design, data science, data delivery, quoting, and forecasting guidance to BDS and work closely with the Project Coordination team to ensure customer satisfaction and streamlined processes
Bring creative solutions to clients and be able to understand the value drivers within their organizations
Particularly focus on helping to examine and penetrate new segments and future growth accounts in the mid-plex arena
Maintain knowledge of competitive products and technologies
Work closely with the Field Marketing team to develop and help execute campaigns around mid-plex
Work with global mid-plex product management to maintain fluid cross-communication and implementation
Qualifications/Skills
BS, MS or PhD in Biology or related field
Experience in selling to a senior level is a necessity
Evidence of capability to perform in a customer-facing role
Evidence of capability in sales management
Technical experience with proteomics or biomarker discovery
A relevant network of contacts across the industry
Ability to work flexibly between a home office and in the field with clients
Ability to travel with a broad selection of reps
Ability to attend national trade shows when needed
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills
Strong work ethic and desire to succeed
Self-starter that has an entrepreneurial spirit and drive
Ability to prioritize and manage multiple tasks
Able to meet or exceed revenue targets
Ability to work well in a team environment
Self-confident and outgoing personality
Open to learning and synthesizing from teammates
Willing to teach members of team and share relevant experiences

Title: Recruiter | Stockholm
Description:
Are you an entrepreneurial Recruiter who would like to kick-start the Recruitment Team in ADC’s Sweden office? Does finding the right job for the right candidate interests you? If you are ready to establish a team and accelerate our growth, this is the opportunity for you!

Amsterdam Data Collective is a full-stack data-science agency that helps build data-driven organizations. Our team are exceptional at understanding what drives decision-makers, the context in which an organization operates and the bounds of technology. The ADC community is growing quickly and aspires to maintain a culture in which our people can unleash their full potential. By establishing a culture in which giving and receiving feedback is encouraged, we aim for optimal knowledge transfer and personal growth. We are a fast-growing company of ambitious people, dedicated to helping progressive leaders to shape a positive future.

With our global expansion to Stockholm and Copenhagen, we are looking for Recruiters to build a Recruitment team in the countries and accelerate the growth. At the moment, the Stockholm team is 6 consultants, you will be our first Support Staff to hire the rest!

What you do:
Recruitment Cycle: Responsible for writing the vacancies, sourcing, engaging, screening and guiding talent through the whole candidate journey
Employer branding: Organise and facilitate online and offline employer branding events, and campaign together with the Marketing team
Improvements: Develop and drive continuous improvements that positively impact our application process, ensuring a good candidate experience
Structure: play an active role in structuring and standardising the recruitment cycle, contribute to our ‘Recruitment Playbook’
Stakeholder Management: Organise and coordinate the interview process while managing the expectations of hiring managers/team
ATS: Maintain accurate information using our Application Tracking System (ATS)
Career Event: Collaborate with student associations and execute career events to touch the lives of future generations
Strategy: Contribute and determine the recruitment strategy together with your team, in line with ADC's business needs
Collaborate: Work together with the Recruitment Team, People & Operations, and the Support team

What you bring:
3+ years of Recruitment experience (Consultancy, Tech-Recruitment or similar)
Familiarity with ATS systems is a big plus (We use Recruitee)
Natural networking skills to build great relationships
Excellent written and spoken English (Swedish is a plus)
Passion for recruitment, particularly technical recruitment
Team player attributes
Interest in attracting and recruiting diverse profiles by creating a diverse pipeline of candidates
Drive to continuously improve the candidate journey
High level of self-motivation
You are able to define structure and adapt to change quickly
Project management skills: you are someone who is able to perform and prioritise multiple tasks and demonstrate close attention to detail

What we offer:
Be the first Recruitment Member located in Sweden
A steep learning curve by taking on responsibility from day one
Possibility to build a Recruitment Team in future
Freedom to realise own initiatives and implement your ideas
A training program focused on your self-development, designed to transform people into trusted advisors, specialists, and ADC leaders
A knowledge sharing culture in the form of peer groups, project presentations and Collective Lunch Sharing Sessions
Our Collective Week, a workcation with the entirety of ADC during which we work on pro bono projects and make unforgettable memories
A collective bonus on top of a competitive salary
A lot of social events

What to do next:
If you are inspired by the above, apply from the link below!
For questions, feel free to contact us from recruitment@amsterdamdatacollective.com

Amsterdam Data Collective is an equal opportunity employer. To shape a better future we value diversity and promote equality. No characteristics are discriminated against, as indicated in Directive 2000/78/EC . We encourage and welcome all applications. Additional arrangements or adjustments to support your application can be discussed further.

Title: Cloud Solution Architect – Data & AI
Description:
As a Cloud Solution Architect, you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers make the right decisions and give them a solid foundation to succeed on their journey.
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data has a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
We are partners with different technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of clients and technologies, together with amazing colleagues.
As a Cloud Solution Architect, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing optimal technical solutions.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients in the decision making of which platform and architecture to use
Integration of different data sources, modeling and loading of data
Optimizing different solutions (data warehouse, data lakehouse, machine learning) depending on the purpose
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
What we are looking for:
Hands on experience in setting up cloud architecture in Azure, AWS or GCP
Experience in architecting and designing data solutions using trade-off analysis
Knowledge of different information architecture patterns (e.g. dimensional model, data vault 2.0, data mesh, lakehouse)
Experience in DevOps tools including version control (Git), CI/CD pipelines and infrastructure as code (Terraform)
Experience in architecture governance and architecture documentation
Familiar with data management, data security, and access control in the cloud
Prototyping mindset and familiar with Python, Pyspark and SQL
Experience working with streaming data
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills.
What we see as qualifying:
Cloud architect certification or Databricks certification or willingness to undergo one on joining
Evidence of architectural trade off analysis
Hands on experience for designing data ingestion and transformation patterns in the cloud
DataOps solution design experience (observability, error handling)
Experience designing storage topologies, data models and optionally understanding of domain driven design
Experience working with cloud storage, cloud data pipeline tools, CDC tools and data catalogues
Stakeholder management

Title: SALESFORCE DEVELOPER, DISCOVER
Description:
City: Solna
Job Function: IT
ARE YOU A TRAVELER?
Since 1946, we have kept Scandinavia connected to the world and the world to Scandinavia. We have been frontrunners in the air – but the future we head into is ever-changing. We need to be one step ahead.

Which is why we are now making the largest move within Digital and IT in the history of SAS;
We will employ 100 new people working with data engineering, data science, UX design, front- and backend development and more, to a new inhouse department – leading the way for aviation into the future. Our ambitions transcend those of our industry – and this team will be the center of our most accelerated technological transformation so far.
About the role
You could call it a Salesforce Marketing Cloud developer but we’re looking for an enabler of customer journeys. We want to offer our travelers personalized journeys driven by important life and travel events. You will have a key role in making this happen.


As a Salesforce Marketing Cloud Developer, you will enable the seamless transition of data from various customer data sources and help transform it to personalized journeys in the Marketing Cloud. You will act as an evangelist for Salesforce Marketing Cloud and carry out hands-on development on the platform. Together with the team you will support marketeers throughout their Journey building process.

Enable cross channel customer journeys using Journey Builder
Optimize data model for segmentation and personalization
Work with inbound and outbound data integrations
Process customer and platform data using SQL
Create dynamic, personalized marketing assets using SSJS and Ampscript
Build Marketing Cloud web experience (data forms, custom preference pages)
Work through and resolve scenarios using REST and SOAP API
About you
You’re passionate about digital marketing and developing solutions on top of the Salesforce ecosystem. You have a strong understanding of best practices, functionality and technical capabilities of Salesforce Marketing Cloud such as developing complex automations in Automation Studio, creating Cloud Pages for multiple channels and building up dynamic, personalized email content in Email Studio.

Experience in front-end development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)
Scripting and personalisation utilizing Ampscript and SSJS
Experience with API integrations (REST/SOAP)
Working knowledge of SQL
Understanding of Agile practices and associated tools (Jira/Azure DevOps or similar)
General understanding of key digital marketing trends
Experience with complex data structures, data modelling and databases
Marketing Cloud Email Specialist certification required
Marketing Cloud Developer certification preferred
About us
We engage a Digital First mindset, encouraging a fail fast, learn fast environment with cross functional and agile teams focusing on fast delivery, quick iterations, and collaboration. We develop in-house products with usage of modern, innovative technologies allowing for freedom to bring in own ideas and creating a real impact. We offer an exciting setting surrounded by industry talent, where you are encouraged to challenge the status quo while simultaneously getting the support you need to develop your desired skills and expertise
Purposeful: Be part of a historical transformation on a continuous journey to create a new and seamless way to travel, with opportunities to solve challenges that no one has cracked before
Flexible: Office, Home, Norway, Copenhagen – wherever you are, Scandinavia is your home and flexibility is at our core
Adventurous: We grow by making the world smaller. Discounted airline tickets providing you, your family and friends to travel the world at great prices.
Personal: Opportunity to work on many customer & business challenges and initiatives
Innovative: Building in-house development of products allows for freedom to bring in own ideas
Ownership: Opportunity of bringing initiatives from ideas into end-point delivery
Other of importance
Deadline for application: 13th of February 2023. We process applications on an ongoing basis. The position is based in Stockholm, Sweden at the SAS headquarters at Frösundavik.

Title: Head of Product - Financial Management, Reporting and Analytics (all genders)
Description:
THE ROLE & THE TEAM
Over the last years, we learned that solving fulfillment-related challenges for the good of our customers helps us to fuel the growth of our platform. With more partners in Partner Program and Connected Retail joining our platform, we have been developing and testing additional fulfillment services tailored to their needs.
The Connected Network department is responsible for all partner-facing Zalando Logistics Solutions. By unifying these services under a single umbrella, we provide a more holistic approach to deliver the optimal fulfillment solution to meet our partners' needs, and leverage common services to enable scalable growth.
As the Head of Product - Financial Management, Reporting and Analytics, you are responsible for the full product vision, strategy, and execution. You will have full ownership of the problem space and solutions based on deep knowledge of the end user (both internal and external users), data usage of our products, industry and competitive insights, and business strategy. This role will have direct responsibility for Product resources and collaborate closely with designers, researchers, data analysts, program management and operations to discover and build an innovative and optimized fulfillment platform for our partners. You will also collaborate closely with internal stakeholders and teams to deliver compelling solutions and insights to our internal users.
INCLUSIVE BY DESIGN
At Zalando, our vision is to be the Starting Point for Fashion - one that is inclusive by design. We only assess candidates based on qualifications, merit, and business needs. We welcome applications from people of all gender identities, sexual orientations, personal expressions, racial identities, ethnicities, religious beliefs, and disability statuses. We only want to know why you're great for this role, so please avoid including your picture, age, and marital status in your CV as well.
We want to provide you with a great candidate experience. Please feel free to inform us of any accommodations you may need, so we can best support and assist you throughout the hiring process.
do.BETTER - our diversity & inclusion strategy: https://corporate.zalando.com/en/diversity-inclusion
Our employee resource groups: https://corporate.zalando.com/en/diversity-inclusion/our-employee-resource-groups
WHAT WE'D LOVE YOU TO DO (AND LOVE DOING)
You'll work with Product, Engineering, Operations and Commercial teams to define and drive the long-term vision and product strategy for the areas of Financial Management, Reporting and Analytics, and Data Science aligned with the overall vision and strategy for Fulfillment. You will transfer the vision and strategy into actionable roadmaps.
You'll take ownership and deliver initiatives to improve data accuracy and transparency and increase automation. You will own providing internal and external stakeholders with data driven recommendations and actionable performance insights to enable these teams to effectively steer and grow their business with Zalando.
You'll contribute to the Product Management community at Zalando and help shape its future.
You'll inspire, consult and empower your team and stakeholders.
You'll discover and validate customer problems and commercial opportunities based on rigorous product management frameworks and techniques.
You'll utilize data to drive decision making, evolve the solutions to be data driven and automated.
You'll reinforce a constant and dedicated focus on our customers and partners and how to solve the right problems.
You will provide direct coaching and support of Product Managers, helping guide their careers and growth.
WE'D LOVE TO MEET YOU IF
You are an experienced, data-driven and collaborative Product Management practitioner and leader.
You have experience developing B2B, Financial services, Supply Chain or Logistics products across multiple platforms.
You have excellent verbal and written communication skills and ability to work across multiple teams, align goals and deliverables and drive overall success independent of organizational boundaries.
You have experience of owning the long and medium-term vision and development roadmap for products with a multi-year horizon for reaching the full vision.
You know how to measure the success of your product and continuously iterate to improve it for the benefit of our customers and our business.
You have experience of managing senior stakeholders for alignment and buy-in to deliver impact.
If you think you have what it takes, we encourage you to apply even if you don't meet every single requirement. You may just be the right candidate for this or other roles!
OUR OFFER
Zalando provides a range of benefits. Ask your Talent Acquisition Partner to learn more about what we offer.
Learn all about Zalando and our values here: https://jobs.zalando.com/en/?gh_src=22377bdd1us

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Background
We help our customers modernize software application delivery to the cutting edge with Infrastructure as Code, containers, and private/public Cloud Computing. Today the majority of IT landscapes consist of static instances on Windows and Linux servers, with dependencies towards core applications still running on legacy hardware. At ICG we employ the experts that turn these old landscapes into an efficient and secure software delivery machine.
Together with Driven By Data, Innovation Capacity Group form a corporate group that combines our knowledge.
At Driven by Data, data is king and facts are unquestionable. We are a knowledge company active within the fields of operational intelligence, cybersecurity, and event-driven automation. Leveraging our expertise in these domains, we guide and advise our customers in their journey to become data-driven.
Profile
We are looking for a new colleague with experience from large corporations or authorities. You have a solid understanding of everything from networking to operating systems.
Besides the technical skills, you need to be an established consultant used to working in large-scale IT environments.
In this position, you will be teaming up with one of our seniors and over the coming years become a world-class Data Analysis and Cyber Security Expert.
Skills
AWS/Azure/GCP
Tensorflow, Keras, Jupyter m.fl.
Log and data tools such as ELK, Splunk, LogRythm or LogPoint
Time-series databases such as InfluxDB, Prometheus, Timestream or Druid
Python or other programming languages
Linux and Unix experience
Apache Airflow, Spark, Kafka, and/or Nifi
Experience in Machine Learning, Data Engineering, or Data Science is a plus.
What we offer you
We focus on the people. We aim to be the best Consultant Employer there is. Money and company growth are secondary to staff happiness, education, and knowledge sharing. We are built on a solid foundation of knowledge, sharing, and fun at work.
We expect all employees to be part of this culture.
Ask questions and be hungry for more knowledge
Hold seminars and attend national and international conferences
Arrange and take part in spontaneous activities
Come with us on our yearly international trips
Participation in our competence jam sessions, conferences, and trips

Title: Senior Pythonutvecklare
Description:
Vi söker erfarna Pythonutvecklare till vårt team med Data Scientists och programmerare. Du kommer att arbeta med att designa, utveckla och driftsätta lösningar, baserat på bland annat Linux, Kubernetes och Google Cloud.
Majoriteten av våra projekt baseras på artificiell intelligens, maskininlärning och data science men vi utvecklar även tjänster inom web crawling.
Din bakgrund kan antingen vara att du är en mycket duktig programmerare som är van att sätta projekt i produktion, eller så är du specialiserad inom maskininlärning, med erfarenhet av hur det implementeras i kod. Du kan ta dig an och avsluta uppgifter med stor grad av självständighet. Eftersom vi är ett litet växande företag behöver du ha en bred teknisk kompetens och vara flexibel i din projekt.
Du har minst 3 års professionell erfarenhet av:
Python 3, Linux, Git, Kubernetes and Docker, Databaser, Webbramverk (tex. Flask), Moln (tex. Google Cloud eller Azure), ML-ramverk (tex. Pytorch)
Extra glada blir vi om du kan visa på en stark AI/ML- och/eller statistikbakgrund.
Våra projekt
Hos Tenfifty får du arbeta med en mängd utmanande och roliga AI-projekt. På senare tid har vi till exempel tagit fram lösningar baserat på speech to text, Video OCR, rekommendationssystem, prisprediktioner och prognoser. Normalt är att vi jobbar med två utvecklare och projektadministratör som ett miniteam i varje projekt men vi diskuterar och löser problem tillsammans i hela utvecklingsteamet, där det finns mycket djup och bred kunskap.
Tenfifty som arbetsplats
Vi erbjuder en mycket trevlig arbetsmiljö med stor grad av frihet i arbetet. Sedan Tenfifty startades har vi erbjudit våra anställda att arbeta på distans tre dagar i veckan, kombinerat med två dagar på kontoret där vi träffas och stämmer av, en lösning som ger oss det bästa av båda världar.
Vi är en platt organisation med korta snabba beslutsvägar. Vi tar oss bara an projekt som vi verkligen tror på och vi är av uppfattningen att den bästa arbetsmiljön är den där alla kan fokusera på det de är bäst på.
Vi har en robust process för kunskapsdelning och du kommer att arbeta i en trevlig miljö tillsammans med väldigt skickliga Pythonprogrammerare och Machine Learning experter.
Övriga förmåner inkluderar att du får välja din egen utrustning (hårdvara, OS, IDE etc), ett bra pensionsupplägg och friskvårdsbidrag.

Title: Power BI & Power Apps Specialist
Description:
We are seeking an experienced Power BI & Power Apps Specialist for our client in Stockholm.
The main part of the work will be focused on developing one or more PowerApps to be consumed by users in the production unit.
Expert skills in working with PowerBI and developing PowerApps is a must. Prior experience in creating advanced dashboards, data entry user interfaces, and reports is also required. Some backend work, preparing and ingesting the data will also be required, but mainly we expect this work to be handled through our Data Platform Team.
You will be responsible for presenting operational data, from the mail and logistics domain.
The position includes working closely with the rest of the team, gathering user interface requirements from business experts, and working with other teams such as Data Platform team to identify and solve issues and to use the data in a user-friendly way. It also includes building and designing experiments to merge, manage, interrogate, and extract data to supply tailored reports to business experts.
We are looking for an experienced and autonomous developer working with Power Apps to create a user interface and to visualize the output of a data product relating to workforce demand. You will work as part of a team and interact with business users to understand the requirements.
Main duties and deliverables

The candidate will develop a Power App (with PowerBI integration) that will involve visual reports, KPI scorecards, and dashboards for interfacing with a new demand planning data tool. Both UIs for data input and dashboards for visualization of the result is part of the tasks.

Key experience and qualifications required
5 years experience working with business intelligence, analytics, front-end development, ETL-processes, data engineering, data science or similar
Experience developing in PowerApps and the Azure tech stack
Experience creating dashboards, reports and visualizations in PowerBI
Experience creating user interfaces for data entry in Power Apps
Analytical thinking for translating data into informative reports and visuals
Valuable experience and qualifications
Connecting data sources, importing data, and transforming data for visualizing the outcome of data modeling
Developing visual reports, KPI scorecards, and dashboards using PowerBI desktop
Capable of implementing role based secuity on data with an understanding of application security models in PowerApps / PowerBI
Experience with DAX queries in PowerBI
xperience in data warehousing – preferably within the Azure tech stack, e.g. Azure Synapse
Language
Fluent English. Swedish is valuable but not compulsory.
Working arrangements

Start ASAP, initially for 6 months but likely to be long-term.
Hybrid working after agreement.

You must have an existing right to work in Sweden without sponsorship in order to apply.

Title: Senior Data Engineer
Description:
Substorm is a consulting and development company in the field of Intelligent Automation. We create customer value in the Digitization area through change management and technology development. We offer understandable solutions and create data-driven insights with the help of techniques from AI / machine learning, RPA and Business Intelligence. We also conduct research activities within Agenda 2030's global goals for sustainable development, specifically No. 5 Gender equality and No. 9 Sustainable industry, innovations and infrastructure.
We drive change and are eager to co-create benefits with modern technology and smart analytics. We bring fun and efficiency back to our customers daily work, and do it with algorithms, automation and extensive business knowledge.

We have offices across Sweden, from Luleå in the North to Stockholm and Gothenburg in the South - and we want to grow!

We are now looking for Senior Data Engineers to join our team.

You will work with data processing and data warehousing and help build our infrastructure for use both as stand-alone services and as part of bigger Machine Learning projects. You will be part of implementing the architecture enabling our data science projects, our business reporting requirements and our visualization needs.
We believe that you have worked as a Data Engineer for a few years and that you have previous experience of consulting in the field. You have a university degree in data engineering, computer science, machine learning or other relevant fields, or have proven experience achieved by other means. We also believe that you:
Have strong experience in advanced data structures, distributed computing, ETL/ELT, SQL and SQL transformations
Have strong experience working with cloud based platforms and services
Are excited to take ownership and share knowledge with colleagues and customers
Have an agile mindset and know and care about a CI/CD way of working


It is a plus if you have knowledge of Machine Learning tools and algorithms, and experience in building and designing large scale end-to-end applications and services.
As a person, you are enterprising, solution-oriented and caring. You can explain business value and benefits with your ideas and solutions in a professional way, are a true team player and are always ready for learning new technologies and skills.

Our company is growing fast and offer great opportunities for learning and variety in your work.

Candidates are expected to hold a valid work permit for the EU and Sweden.


More about Substorm
Substorm consists of developers, business analysts as well as automation strategists. We organize our work based on the customer’s need but preferably we deliver as a team. Technology is in our backbone, but we always adjust to our customers actual need. Our day to day work is fast-paced and exciting with a lot of heart and engagement. Conferences overseas, after works and other more or less spontaneous events spices up our work - and we have a lot of fun together!

Title: Senior Verification and Validation Engineer for...
Description:
Zenseact proudly creates software in order to make safe and intelligent mobility real for everyone and everywhere. Team HADES (Highly Autonomous Driving: Exposure & Scenarios), a truly agile team, actively contributes to Zenseact’s mission by developing data-driven, scenario-based verification and validation of our autonomous driving software.
So how do we know which scenarios the vehicle will be exposed to within its operational design domain, and how do we ensure that the software can handle statistically relevant scenarios? Solving these challenges is one of the keys to achieving safe autonomous driving. Therefore, the team exploits data science to create representative models of real-world traffic and to explore the scenario state space.
Your mission and day-to-day tasks:
You will work with large data, closed-loop simulations, test case generation, and statistical modeling to develop data-driven frameworks for scenario-based verification and validation of autonomous driving. You will also work closely with feature developers, data science experts, and other stakeholders.
Your work could include:
Designing a scenario ontology for scenario-based verification of AD software.
Developing methods to automatically generate critical synthetic test cases from the scenario database.
Evaluating the safety norm compliance of our AD software.
Developing falsification algorithms for a motion planner.
Supporting the team with your knowledge in scenario-based verification.
Exploring the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence for scenario-based verification.
Together with the team, you will achieve something that has never been done before. You will get the opportunity to work on complex tasks and expand your knowledge every single day.
We see that you have:
High academic background, at least an MSc in a relevant engineering discipline like Computer Science.
Experience with verification and validation of ADAS/AD software, in particular scenario-based verification.
Strong programming skills in Python.
Would be a plus if there is experience with any of the following:
Data analysis, statistics, reliability analysis.
Automatic generation of safety-critical scenarios, e.g., reinforcement learning.
Knowledge of safety standards, especially ISO/PAS 21448 (SOTIF) and optionally ISO 26262 (Functional Safety).
Autonomous driving software stack, like trajectory planning.
Who are you?
Team spirit is really important at Zenseact. We would love to see that you enjoy collaborating with your team members, other teams, and stakeholders. You should have great communication skills and a solution-driven mindset. You will thrive at work with us when you love being creatively combined with an ability to bring tasks to completion. We also expect you to strive for continuous improvement, embrace an open feedback culture and dare to fail.
The rest, you tell us.

How do we work?
Flexible-remote way of working: Zenseact has a flexible and modern approach, thus is happy to offer to its employees the possibility for a combination of work at the office and from home. This doesn't include fully remote work from outside Sweden/China.

More about Zenseact

Zenseact’s purpose is to make safe and intelligent mobility real, for everyone, everywhere. We develop the complete software stack for ADAS and AD, from sensing to actuation. Our focus is to build a single cutting-edge software platform in order to serve various levels of autonomy and offer unequaled scalability at the same time. We operate out of Gothenburg, Sweden and Shanghai, China. Zenseact’s first self-driving deployment will be launched on the next-generation vehicle platform from Volvo Cars.

Self-driving cars, when real, is estimated to reduce fatal car accidents with more than 85%, saving more than 50,000 persons from dying in car accidents caused by human errors each year. We feel that is a goal worth pursuing.

But technology, software, tools and datasets would not mean much without the best people behind the wheel to drive them. At Zenseact, some five hundred of the best engineering minds globally, stationed across two continents, are collaborating with the same passion: to bring autonomous driving to the streets for real and create a safer journey for everyone. This is part of our culture and how we work, develop and grow together.
Zenseact works proactively to create a culture of diversity and inclusion, where individual differences are appreciated and respected. To drive innovation we see diversity as an asset, which means we value and respect differences in gender, race, ethnicity, religion or other belief, disability, sexual orientation or age etc.

Interviews are held on a continuous basis, so we highly recommend that you submit your application at your earliest convenience.

Title: PRODUCT MANAGER
Description:
OVERVIEW:
We are looking for a Senior Product Manager that will join the Data Management Product Area responsible for our Data Quality, Management and Governance.
You will closely work two squads focusing on Data observability and governance and drive the strategy, roadmap and ship products.
Above all, your work will impact the way the world experiences music.
WHAT YOU’LL DO:

Work closely with other Product Managers in the Data Platform group to identify and address gaps in the client’s offering with the goal of providing a world-class data development experience at the client

Collaborate with product, engineering, and data science teams to gather feedback and requirements for the client’s data processing needs
Define and drive overall product vision, strategy and metrics for our data observability and governance teams, inspiring our teams to build great products and address gaps in the client’s offering with the goal of providing a world-class data development experience
Work passionately to ensure your team is focusing on the right things, balancing short versus long term needs. A healthy balance of innovation, support and maintenance is key for all successful teams at the client.
