Title: AWS Data Engineer
Description:
Company Description
Devoteam A Cloud Sweden is the most recent addition to the Swedish Devoteam family. We specialize in bringing together and growing AWS expertise - we’re a team of curious, bold and brilliant people. At A Cloud, we combine startup flexibility and creativity, with the operational and capital support of an enterprise. At Devoteam we collaborate with our customers in finding the next innovative solution that will support the customer to achieve better business results.
We always base our advice and implementations on proven best practices. Working as our customers’ trusted architects, we secure the platform for the future and provide solutions to support their business demands. We work agile with prototyping to show early effects and opportunities.
We specialize in Edge Computing including IoT, Serverless, Data Streaming and Analytics, Modernization & Migration as well as Security.
Job Description
We are seeking a skilled Data Engineer to join our delivery team. You will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining data pipelines and data architectures to support data-driven decision making within our clients’ organization. You will work closely with Data Scientists, Data Analysts, and other stakeholders to identify and prioritize data needs, and you will be responsible for implementing scalable and reliable data pipelines, lakes and warehouses to support these needs.

Key responsibilities:
Design and build data pipelines and data architectures.
Collaborate with Data Scientists, Data Analysts, and other stakeholders to identify and prioritize data needs.
Ensure that data pipelines are scalable, maintainable, and reliable.
Troubleshoot and resolve data pipeline issues as needed.
Stay up-to-date with new technologies and best practices in data engineering, especially on AWS.

This is a hands-on role and will require a great deal of “can-do” attitude!
We have a hybrid office working model and like to occasionally meet the clients’ team at their offices.
Qualifications
We believe that you are open-minded to new ideas and flexible when meeting new challenges to succeed in this role. You have the ability to work independently and prioritize tasks effectively to deliver on time and with quality. You enjoy collaborating and are comfortable sharing your knowledge with your colleagues and clients.

Key requirements:
You have been working at least 3 years as a Data Engineer, building data pipelines, data lakes, and data warehouses.
Strong programming skills in Python and SQL. Java or Scala is a plus.
Good knowledge of data modeling with techniques/approaches like data vault, snowflake or star.
Experience in AWS services such as AWS Kinesis, AWS Glue, AWS S3, AWS Redshift, and AWS Athena
Experience with data mesh architecture is a plus
BS degree in a relevant field (e.g. Computer Science, Data Science, etc.) or equivalent work experience.

You are fluent in English in order to communicate with various stakeholders both technical and business oriented.
Additional Information

At Devoteam Stockholm you get:
Challenging and rewarding assignments; many of them end-to-end
Wellness grants for sports activities (5000 SEK/year)
Passionate and skilled colleagues
Human-centric and value-based culture
Variety of social events

About Devoteam A Cloud
Devoteam A Cloud is a Premier Partner to AWS with 4 competencies, 400+ AWS certified experts and 700+ certifications. In 2020, Devoteam A Cloud trained over 1000+ people.
At Devoteam, we deliver innovative technology consulting for businesses. As a pure player for Digital Transformation of large organizations across EMEA, our 10000+ professionals are dedicated to ensuring our clients win their digital battles. With a unique transformation DNA, we connect business and technology. Present in over 20 countries in Europe and the Middle East, and drawing on more than 20 years of experience, we shape Technology for People, so it creates value for our clients, for our partners and for our employees. Our mission is to build cultures of innovation at companies by transforming the way they work and by elevating their customer experiences.
We are looking for people with big ambitions, who want to grow with us and help companies build a culture of innovation with AWS solutions.
At Devoteam, we share our knowledge, learn from each other and from other experts by giving or listening to talks, participating in Hackathons, taking hands-on classes and getting certified.

A fair chance.
Devoteam is open to applications from all sections of society. We believe diverse teams help us make better products. We welcome all people regardless of age, gender, experience and background.
If you can see yourself in this role and feel you can bring value and a unique perspective to Devoteam, we encourage you to send us your application - even if you do not necessarily meet all the above requirements.
We apply continuous recruitment, so make sure to send in your application as soon as possible, given that Devoteam A Cloud’s recruitment process allows us to hire someone else before the last application day.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Är byggandet av data pipelines din grej? Vi söker dig som är duktig på att bygga ramverk för att andra skall kunna analysera data och du förstår även vikten av datadriven utveckling för att skapa framtidens produkter och tjänster.

Din framtida utmaning

Just nu ser vi ett uppsving i antalet utmaningar som är kopplade till datahantering. Datainsamlingen i sig är oftast straight-forward, och utmaningen ligger således i att förädla datamängden och göra den användbar. Det kan handla om allt från att extrahera, städa, sortera, och filtrera data till att använda statistiska verktyg för att hitta nya samband och visualisera detta med hjälp av BI-system. Din uppgift blir att förse övriga organisationen med rätt förutsättningar att kunna jobba datadrivet i sin utveckling.

Den du är idag

Som person är du engagerad, analytisk, och strävar efter att leverera ditt bästa resultat varje gång. Du är kreativ och nyfiken inför uppdragets behov och kan snabbt anpassa dig till olika situationer. Du tycker att det är spännande när allting inte är bestämt på förhand och sporras av att få sätta dig in i nya sammanhang. Du har fenomenal fingertoppskänsla och har förståelse för verksamhetens behov, för att kunna hitta den rätta lösningen för att komma framåt. Du är social och gillar att arbeta i team och ser spännande utmaningar i de möjligheter som erbjuds.

Krav

Utbildningsbakgrund inom Data, Fysik, Teknisk Matematik eller Statistik
Givetvis kan du programmera
Vi söker dig som kan åtminstone ett av nedan koncept

AWS, GCP, Azure
Azure-moduler såsom Data Factory/Event Hub/Service Bus
Spark, Hadoop
Power BI, SAS
Andra koncept
Vi ser med intresse på om du har något av följande erfarenheter med dig

Erfarenhet av dataanalys, data science
Erfarenhet av att arbeta agilt
Ansökan

Om du är intresserad av att bli en del av vår gemenskap på Infotiv så tycker vi att du ska ansöka till oss! Vi önskar höra mer om:

Dina erfarenheter; vad du har gjort tidigare i livet och vad du önskar göra framöver
Vem du är utanför arbetet
Eventuellt några rader om vad som gör dig till just den du är
Vilka vi är

Infotiv TechDev består idag av 70 ingenjörer, där våra uppdrag täcker alla aspekter av mjukvaruutvecklingsprocessen, från koncept och design till implementation och slutverifiering. Vi värdesätter ett öppet klimat och stöttar våra ambitiösa medarbetare. Som teknikkonsult hos Infotiv är man aldrig ensam och man har flertalet aktiviteter att engagera sig i, både kompetensbyggande och sociala.

Som teknikkonsult på Infotiv är du en del av ett företag som vårdar människorna som arbetar här. Företaget karaktäriseras av korta beslutsvägar och en familjär atmosfär, vilket gör att din närmaste chef har stora möjligheter att själv bestämma. Vi vet vad uppdragen går ut på, vilka utmaningar som finns och vilka egenskaper som uppskattas av uppdragsgivaren. Ledorden varmt hjärta, skarp hjärna genomsyrar vår organisation och samtliga våra medarbetare. Givetvis har vi bra lön och kollektivavtal.

Låter detta intressant, så tveka inte att ansöka redan idag. Vi genomför intervjuer löpande och tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas innan sista ansökningsdatum. Vi hoppas att du vill vara med och växa med oss!

Title: Säljande affärsutvecklare av AI på riktigt
Description:
Artificiell intelligens kommer att förändra i princip alla samhällssektorer framåt. Denna enorma potential har redan öppnat för helt nya affärsområden för företagen och detta tillsammans med att fler AI-tekniker mognar ökar möjligheten att möta många viktiga behov på marknaden. Tenfifty utvecklar skräddarsydda lösningar, byggda på avancerad AI-teknik inom ett flertal olika specialistområden såsom neurala nätverk, djupinlärning, boostade träd, bayesiansk statistik, simuleringar och mycket mer. Alla ovannämnda områden och olika kundleveranser har det gemensamt, att det är fullt fokus att saker skall tas i skarp drift hos Tenfiftys kunder, dvs AI på riktigt.
Som Sveriges mest erfarna leverantör av tjänster för artificiell intelligens, söker vi nu en ny kollega i form av en driven säljande affärsutvecklare som vill vara en del av vårt briljanta gäng och bidra med nya viktiga affärer i vår framgångsresa.
Du har troligen en bakgrund bestående av några års erfarenhet av teknisk lösningsförsäljning, gärna med ett redan upparbetat nätverk av beslutsfattare som grund. Vidare är du kvicktänkt och lättlärd med en förmåga att analysera och förstå en kunds problem och hur det kan lösas med hjälp av specialistkompetens. Vi blir extra glada om du har erfarenhet av försäljning av projekt baserade på data science- och/eller maskininlärning. Du kommer få möjlighet till egen påverkan i rollen, där du arbetar i nära samarbete med mycket kompetenta och engagerade kollegor, och med en gedigen referenslista av riktigt nöjda kunder som grund.
Tenfifty har sedan starten 2014 varit helt självfinansierade, vi har haft en positiv och stabil tillväxttakt och med hjälp av en lyckad försäljning tillsammans skapat en mycket god lönsamhet i företaget. Vi är en platt organisation med korta beslutsvägar. Hos oss återfinns en kunskaps- och teknikbaserad, prestigelös miljö med en stor portion ödmjukhet och respekt för varandra. Vi satsar på en verksamhetsstruktur där alla gör det de är bäst på och trivs med vilket skapar arbetsglädje och är en viktig hörnsten i vår framgång.
Är du intresserad av att bli en del av ett mycket bra team och vara med på resan när vi bygger Tenfifty vidare men nya spännande kunder och lösningar? Då vill vi att du skickar in din ansökan där du presenterar dig själv och berättar varför du tror att just du skulle passa i rollen som affärsutvecklare hos oss.
Om du har några frågor kring den här tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta Kristina Bjurström, 0723-41 81 41 alternativt via mail kristina.bjurstrom@tenfifty.io.

Title: Azure Data Engineer - Gothenburg
Description:
As an Azure Data Engineer you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards data-driven decision-making. We are all passionate about data!
What You’ll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
The position as Data Engineer will provide you the opportunity to work in a team-based environment together with other colleagues specialized within the same field as yourself.
As a Data Engineer, you will help our clients towards data-driven decision-making, by developing optimal technical solutions.
We are partners with different providers of technical platforms and tools such as Azure, Snowflake, Databricks, AWS & Google Cloud, hence you will be given the flexibility to work both with a variation of both technologies and clients. We work in a broad field in just about every industry and have a mix of projects.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Preparing data for analytical or operational uses and build data pipelines to bring together data from different source systems - to facilitate analyzing data at scale
Structure, integrate, consolidate and cleanse data
Work closely with data science teams, improving data transparency and enabling businesses to make more trustworthy business decisions
Collaboration with skilled colleagues and our clients
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you come from a strong Data Engineering experience.
You need to have:
Minimum 2 years of cloud experience (Azure, AWS or GCP)
Minimum 2 years of experience in ETL-tools such as Azure Data Factory
Experience in Data Lake or Lakehouse Architecture
Excellent SQL syntax skills
Information- and Data Warehouse modeling
Good skills in code versioning such as GIT GitHub, DevOps
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Experience from platform modernization
Experience from Tabular cubes and DAX
Databricks
Snowflake
Experience in Snowpro, Matillion or DBT
Data vault modeling
Agile work process

Title: DNS Research Engineer
Description:
Internetstiftelsen har ett samhällsviktigt uppdrag – vi ser till att internet i Sverige fungerar genom vårt ansvar för toppdomänen .se och driften av .nu, vi driver identitetsfederationer inom skola, vård och omsorg och vi folkbildar i frågor om internet och digitalisering.
DNS Labs är ett litet team inom Internetstiftelsen som fokuserar på forskning och utveckling inom DNS-området. Vi är specialister inom DNS och väldigt engagerade i vårt uppdrag. Att vi nu rekryterar en DNS Research Engineer till teamet är ett steg mot en ännu mer datadriven organisation.
Vill du precis som vi bidra till ett godare och starkare internet i Sverige så är det här jobbet för dig!
Om tjänsten
Som DNS Research Engineer kommer du att jobba med utgångspunkt i data och forskning för att bidra till stabilitet och säkerhet inom DNS på Internetstiftelsen. Vi förväntar oss att du kommer bidra med följande i teamet:
Föreslå förbättringar baserat på dataanalys och forskningsprojekt
Delta aktivt i lokala och internationella konferenser inom vår bransch
Leda tekniska projekt
Dela din kunskap med kollegor (både på Internetstiftelsen och i branschen i stort)
Är du rätt person?
Vi söker dig som har et stort intresse samt djup kunskap inom DNS. Du kan förklara tekniskt komplexa saker på ett tydligt och koncist sätt. Du är en god kommunikatör och är bekväm med att tala inför publik på både svenska och engelska. Vi tror också att du uppfyller följande kvalifikationer för att passa i denna roll:
MSc/PhD inom relevant akademiskt område
Dokumenterad erfarenhet inom Data Science
Erfarenhet av nätverk och applikationer för kritisk infrastruktur
Erfarenhet av olika skriptspråk
Bekväm att arbeta med Linux, DNS/DNSSEC, TLS, BGP och andra relaterade standarder
Ett av våra viktigaste kärnvärden är att alla vi som jobbar på Internetstiftelsen älskar internet, och vi förväntar oss att du också gör det. Om du känner igen dig i den beskrivningen kommer du att pass väl in i vår kultur!
Övrig information
Tjänsten är placerad på vårt huvudkontor som ligger vid vattnet på Hammarby kaj 10 i Hammarby Sjöstad, Stockholm. Vi tillämpar en hybridmodell för vår arbetsvecka med möjlighet att jobba på distans tre dagar per vecka. Tjänsten omfattar heltid och är en tillsvidareanställning med inledande provanställning.
Tillträde så snart som möjligt med hänsyn till eventuell uppsägningstid.
Om Internetstiftelsen:
Internetstiftelsen är en oberoende, affärsdriven och allmännyttig organisation. Vi verkar för ett internet som bidrar positivt till människan och samhället.
Vi ansvarar för den svenska toppdomänen .se och för driften av toppdomänen .nu. Intäkterna från affärsverksamheten finansierar en rad satsningar inom forskning och utbildning i syfte att internetanvändare i Sverige ska kunna vidareutveckla sin användning på ett medvetet sätt och att ge kunskap om internetanvändningen i Sverige och digitaliseringens påverkan på samhället. Exempel på våra satsningar är start- och mötesplatsen Goto 10, rapporten Svenskarna och Internet, Digitala lektioner, konferensen Internetdagarna och mätverktyget Bredbandskollen.
Vår vision är att alla i Sverige vill, vågar och kan använda internet.

Title: HPC specialist
Description:
The EuroCC National Competence Center Sweden (ENCCS) is looking for a researcher with a background in natural sciences or data science / machine learning and extensive experience in high performance computing (HPC). ENCCS is a national competence center in HPC, funded by the Swedish Research Council, Vinnova and the EuroHPC JU via the EuroCC project - a network of European national competence centers in HPC. ENCCS is hosted jointly by RISE and Linköping University.
EuroHPC JU is a multi-billion Euro joint undertaking which enables participating countries to coordinate their efforts and share resources in order to build a world-class supercomputing infrastructure and a competitive innovation ecosystem in supercomputing technologies, applications, and skills in Europe.
ENCCS provides a range of services tailored to the national needs of industry, academia, and public administration in Sweden. The aim is to support and further enhance national strengths in high-performance computing (HPC), high-performance data analytics (HPDA), and artificial intelligence (AI). The specific objectives of ENCCS are to:
Develop expertise, knowledge, and support in Sweden to help users make better use of EuroHPCresources.
Assist key user communities in enabling applications on (pre)exa-scale resources.
Advise users on how to achieve scaling and performance for scientific problems on EuroHPC resources.
Guide new industrial users in using HPC.
Support new AI/data analytics applications. Provide training and skill development nationally and throughout Europe.
About the role
You will be working with an agile team of experts with diverse backgrounds and a shared passion for bringing the benefits of HPC to new user groups through teaching and mentoring, awareness creation, consulting and hands-on software support. Specifically, the work includes supporting users in moving to (pre)exa-scale EuroHPC systems, porting and/or optimizing scientific software for HPC in pilot projects as well as teaching workshops and developing training material. The researcher will also contribute to the development and implementation of the ENCCS strategy, including the development of the service portfolio, establishing collaborations and identifying new user communities.
Please note that this position may mean that a security clearance is required, either later in this process or in the future.
About you
A PhD in natural sciences, data science, machine learning or related areas.
Experience in software development for HPC systems.
Experience with GPU programming.
Excellent communication skills in English and (preferably) Swedish.
Strong communication and team working skills. Teaching experience is a plus.
What We Offer
RISE offers an inclusive workplace with a dynamic environment that gives you opportunities for development both professionally and personally. You will work in a team of committed colleagues to tackle exciting societal challenges. If you are an experienced researcher with a background in HPC and have excellent communication skills, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity!
Welcome with your application!
Please submit your application via the form above. For any questions, please contact Thor Wikfeldt (thor.wikfeldt@ri.se or +46 10 228 4679). Last day of application i January 31, 2023. Please not, we do not accept any applications via email.

Title: Payment & Partner Integration Specialist
Description:
Since our first launch in 2016 we have made millions of people in our different core markets curious enough to try BookBeat and spend 600 million hours listening and reading the books in our app. Of the ones that have tried our service, over 700 000 users have made us a natural part of their everyday life and pay for our service every month. But this is just the beginning of our journey! To take the next step and improve the user experience for both new and current users we are now adding a super talent to our Conversion team. Could you be our next colleague?
The Conversion team works with developing BookBeat's user acquisition platforms, user offers, retention, payment solutions, user account handling and customer support platforms. The main stakeholders for Team Conversion are the Marketing & Sales as well as the Expansion teams, but our conversion experts also work cross functionally with many other teams at BookBeat – for instance the app, as we strive for a frictionless experience between the different platforms.
Your primary focus in this role will be on our different payment solutions, both when it comes to direct payments from end users but also third party payment solutions through different partners. If you have over 3 years of experience of working with payment solutions in e.g. an e-commerce company or subscription service that would set you out as our ideal candidate!

You will report to our Head of Expansion & Business Development and primarily work together with the Conversion team, but also close to our development teams as well as our Growth Data Science & Analytics team. The total team at BookBeat has grown to 150 members, and you will work together with 140 of them at our main office at Sveavägen 56 in Stockholm. Your future main stakeholders as well as all of our development teams are also located here.
The role includes, among other things, to:
be responsible for all payment flows and recurring payments
be responsible for new and existing partner integrations
monitor and understand fraud and chargeback performance on a daily basis
assist our Finance team and Customer Service team as well as other team members with queries related to everything concerning payments
research, evaluate and challenge what we should develop within our payment solutions with different stakeholders
work closely with our development teams to make sure that we can turn user stories into launched features
work closely with our data analysts and data scientists to decide what we should focus on and get results of everything we build
We are looking for someone who:
can plan, coordinate and lead projects against deadlines
has a high understanding of the complexities and possibilities in a technical development project
thrives in an agile and fast-moving environment that is shaped by both external and internal circumstances – and is a driving force in pushing through change
chops in where needed and does not hesitate to tackle difficult problems! On the contrary, you’re motivated by solving problems and not letting things fall through the cracks
is fluent in English and Swedish in both speech and writing
is a driven and energetic person who can lead and complete projects successfully
We believe that you:
have at least three years’ experience from a similar role within B2C
have a relevant university education
Are you ready to take on the role of our new Payment Specialist in the Conversion Team? Then submit your application today! If you have any questions, please contact our Head of Expansion & Business Development william.jakoby@bookbeat.com.
As an employee of BookBeat AB, you can enjoy a benefit package that includes the following:
30 days of vacation each year
ITP1 occupational pension
Occupational group life insurance, work injury insurance & business travel insurance
Yearly wellness allowance
‍️ Weekly wellness hour
Working equipment (computer and phone) as well as phone subscription
BookBeat subscription
In addition to our benefits, we’ll also provide you with:
A stable and sustainable work-life balance (we use flex time)
An office located in the heart of Stockholm
‍️ … including access to a full gym complete with a sauna! We also arrange other fun wellness activities, such as our own running club
The opportunity to grow in your role and career, including challenging & educational work tasks as well as opportunities for education
Fun activities together with colleagues! At BookBeat you’ll enjoy weekly Friday afternoon mingles, monthly company breakfasts and other work events such as Holiday & summer parties, and frequent company wide events
The opportunity to explore projects that you might not have time to do in your day-to-day work during Hack Days
Knowledge sharing opportunities, e.g. during our weekly Friday demo where different teams share what they’ve been or will be working on. Knowledge sharing is also an integral part of our everyday work
(Last but definitely not least) A wonderful and skilled team and manager that will support you throughout your employment!
About us
In 2015, we began our journey towards the goal of offering Europe’s leading service for digital books and in 2016, we launched to the public. Now, about 7 years since our broad launch, BookBeat is used by over 700 000 users every month. We are an ever-growing company within the Bonnier Group and all members who join our journey have the possibility to make an impact on our development – both in the short and long run.
Today, Team BookBeat consists of 150 curious and committed doers. Are you interested in becoming part of our team? Wonderful! While our employees are experts at many different areas, we have four core values uniting all of us:

Be great at what you do
Share what you know
Curiosity for our users and us
Build Team BookBeat
In other words: we want our employees to continuously deep dive into and develop within their area(s) of expertise, but also to share that knowledge with their colleagues – we’re all in this together and cooperate (most often a lot) on a daily basis! We’re also looking for employees who are genuinely curious about our users, journey and organization, a curiosity that drives us to always test out new things in our service and to let our users show us if we’re on the right track. Last but definitely not least we want all our employees to contribute to the everyday cooperations and the wellbeing of Team BookBeat – as already mentioned, we’re in this together and we want our team to be healthy and happy at work, and we all contribute to this in different ways.

Title: IT Business Analyst – Volvo Group Connected Solutions
Description:
Sweden
Position Description
By collecting and analyzing data from more than 1 300 000 connected vehicles we make the world of transportation safer, cleaner, and more efficient. Add electrification and automation to the mix, and we are shaping the future of transportation.

This is us, your new colleagues

Volvo Group Connected Solutions is a software company within the Volvo Group with focus on software development, IT architecture and data science. We are around 700 highly skilled employees, working at the forefront of vehicle connectivity. Our main hub and office is located in Lindholmen, Gothenburg, but we also have offices in Silicon Valley and Greensboro in the US, Curitiba in Brazil, Bangalore in India and China.

We want to connect with curious minds who love innovation and are interested in the future of mobility. We are now looking for a IT Business Analyst in the Core Services area, with interest in requirement identification, breakdown and documentation. You will be part of a small and diverse DevOps team that works in two-week sprints and in ten-week program increments.

The role

As a IT Business Analyst, you are the bridge between the customer/stakeholder and the development team, capturing the requirements in terms of WHAT is needed and WHY. You interface with customers and identify their needs. You are responsible for guiding the team towards a solution that supports the business requirements. You interact with various team-members, such as Solution Architects and Software Engineers, to provide the right solutions and expertise. Additionally, you research advanced technology regarding best practices in the field and seek to find cost-effective solutions. We put the emphasis on who you are as a person and we believe that your personality is the major reason for you to succeed in this role.

Key responsibilities
Provide detailed functional and non-functional requirements and specifications for proposed IT solutions including time and scope involved
Work closely with Domain Teams to ensure requirements are refined to the needed degree
Ensure that the solution developed complies with given architecture guidelines, specifications, security, quality and business partner requirements
Document and monitor requirements fulfilment during one time deliveries

Who are you?
University Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering or similar
Documented experience as IT Business Analyst/Solution Engineer/System Analyst
Advanced understanding of business analysis techniques and processes
Ability to work with various departments to facilitate the orderly execution of a project plan
IT product development experience and leadership skills are preferred
Experience from developing IT applications is preferred
Fluent in English, written and spoken

What can we offer you?

You will be part of a high-performing team that creates great results through awesome people with deep skills.
We believe that teamwork is the key to success, and we have a culture where people truly support and help each other.

Some of the other things we offer you:
Inclusive & Diverse culture
Growth & Development through continuous employee dialogue
Flexible workplace
Additional compensation while on parental leave
3000 SEK/Year Fitness Allowance

Welcome to the heart of connectivity at Volvo Group Connected Solutions!

Want to know more? Contact us!
Please contact Johanna Borgudd, Manager Vehicle Communication +46 739-029569

Kindly note that due to GDPR, we will not accept applications via mail. Please use our career site.

About us
The Volvo Group drives prosperity through transport solutions, offering trucks, buses, construction equipment, power solutions for marine and industrial applications, financing and services that increase our customers’ uptime and productivity. Founded in 1927, the Volvo Group is committed to shaping the future landscape of sustainable transport and infrastructure solutions. Countless career opportunities are offered across the group’s leading brands and entities that share a culture of Trust, Passion, High Performance, Change and Customer Success.
www.volvogroup.com/career.
Volvo Group Connected Solutions is a global organization that leads the development of Volvo’s connected services and solutions of tomorrow. We work at the forefront of connectivity by collecting and analyzing data from over 1 000 000 Volvo customer assets. The organization is set-up to deliver competitive offerings, shorten time to market and provide an arena for new service innovations together with customers, partners and the Volvo Group.
Come and visit us online!

Title: DATA SCIENCE LEAD TILL SJ
Description:
I den här rollen är du ansvarig för att samla och utveckla SJ-koncernens Data Scientists genom att både själv driva djupgående initiativ liksom att organisera och stötta data science-arbetet tvärs koncernen. Organisatoriskt tillhör du SJ-koncernens centrala avdelning för Data & Analys och rapporterar till chefen för Data & Analys.
Följ med på vår resa mot ett hållbart samhälle! SJ - Framtidens sätt att resa.
SJ är på en resa. En resa där målet är att bidra till ett hållbart samhälle genom att möjliggöra klimatsmart resande, i Sverige och i Norden. Vägen dit kantas av en mängd spännande möjligheter och utmaningar de kommande åren.
Vi växer och utvecklas inom hela verksamheten. Mångmiljardinvesteringar i nya moderna tåg, investeringar i digitala system för att effektivisera vår verksamhet, kompetensutveckling av vår personal, listan kan göras lång. Allt detta görs med kunden i fokus och med målet att göra det möjligt för fler att göra det hållbara resevalet.
Till huvudkontoret på Vasagatan 10 i Stockholm, söker vi nu en Data Science Lead som en grundläggande del i att etablera SJs Data & Analys-avdelning och genom det bidra till vår långsiktiga framgång.
Arbetet sker dels i nära samarbete med närmsta gruppen, dels med övriga på SJ som arbetar med avancerad/operationaliserad analys. Rollen är en av de första pusselbitarna som läggs för att skapa grunden till ett mer datadrivet SJ och avdelningen Data & Analys har som uppdrag att driva och guida koncernen framåt på den resan. Vi söker därför en driven och erfaren Data Scientist som kan leda i arbetet att låsa upp den outnyttjade potential som finns i våra omfattande datatillgångar.
Vem söker vi?
Vi söker dig med gedigen erfarenhet av avancerad/operationaliserad analys i komplexa och storskaliga miljöer tillsammans med god förmåga och intresse för att leda andra i en virtuell organisation. I botten har du akademisk examen inom matematiktung inriktning, exempelvis ingenjörsutbildning med fokus på matematik, statistik, datavetenskap, data science eller motsvarande. Du har erfarenhet av olika tekniska plattformar och programmeringsspråk och är väl insatt i hur samverkan med systemutvecklare, data engineers och kravställare kan och bör ske i en agil omgivning. Antagligen har du erfarenhet från en mogen kontext sett till förmåga att utvinna värde från data men har ett intresse för att själv vara med och bygga upp något liknande från grunden.
Du är självgående, nyfiken och ansvarstagande samt får energi av att växla mellan mer övergripande strukturella uppgifter och de som kräver en mer handfast och detaljerad insats.
Arbetsbeskrivning
Som Data Science Lead ansvarar du för att etablera, driva och utveckla samarbete i tvärfunktionellt community med de inom SJ som arbetar med data science-relaterade frågor. I detta ingår till en början att samla gruppen och fokusera dess medlemmar till gemensamma arbetssätt och verktyg för att sen tillsammans utforska nya möjligheter. Arbetet innebär även att bidra till den strategiska planen för hur SJs förmåga kopplat till data science ska utvecklas.
Arbetet bygger alltså på kontinuerlig dialog med koncernens alla delar och att identifiera och samla in utvecklingsbehov för att sedan prioritera dessa för genomförande. Du kommer att stödja andra och även driva egna utvecklingsinitiativ, vissa från grunden och andra genom att vidareutveckla och underhålla sedan tidigare framtagna lösningar.
Ambitionen är att på sikt utöka avdelningen Data & Analys med ytterligare Data Scientist-förmåga vilket då kommer innebära att uppgiften som Data Science Lead växer i form av ett arbetsledningsansvar.
Vad kan SJ erbjuda dig?
På SJ ger vi dig goda möjligheter och utrymme att påverka och bidra till utveckling. Det här är en utmanande och intressant roll som erbjuder frihet i kombination med stort ansvar. En roll som bidrar till, och möjliggör, ett hållbart resande. SJs utveckling och tillväxt har varit och förväntas långsiktigt att vara mycket god. Vår flexibilitet och förmåga att anpassa verksamheten till verkligheten har utvecklats till en av bolagets styrkor.
Kontakt
I den här rekryteringen samarbetar SJ med Jefferson Wells. För mer information om tjänsten är du välkommen att kontakta ansvarig rekryteringskonsult Malin Magnusson 076-780 68 64.
Vi ser gärna att du skickar in din ansökan så snart som möjligt dock senast 15 feb.
Välkommen med din ansökan!
SJ vet att mångfald ger fler perspektiv och ökar SJs konkurrenskraft. Vi välkomnar därför sökanden med olika bakgrunder som vill vara med och bidra till ett inkluderande arbetsklimat.
SJ för människor närmare varandra, varje dag.
SJ är ett svenskt reseföretag som erbjuder hållbara tågresor i egen regi och i samarbete med andra. SJ är ett av Sveriges grönaste varumärken och en del av lösningen för att klimatmålen ska nås. Koncernens 5400 medarbetare i Sverige och Norge bidrar alla till ökat tågresande - framtidens sätt att resa.
Som marknadsledande tågoperatör knyter SJ ihop Sverige, Norge, liksom Skandinaviens huvudstäder och varje dag möts våra kunder och medarbetare på någon av våra 1500 avgångar från över 400 stationer. SJ ägs av svenska staten och har som uppdrag att driva lönsam persontrafik på järnväg.

Title: Data Engineer
Description:
Company Description

Devoteam A Cloud Sweden is the most recent addition to the Swedish Devoteam family. We specialize in bringing together and growing AWS expertise - we’re a team of curious, bold and brilliant people. At A Cloud, we combine startup flexibility and creativity, with the operational and capital support of an enterprise. At Devoteam we collaborate with our customers in finding the next innovative solution that will support the customer to achieve better business results.
We always base our advice and implementations on proven best practices. Working as our customers’ trusted architects, we secure the platform for the future and provide solutions to support their business demands. We work agile with prototyping to show early effects and opportunities.
We specialize in Edge Computing including IoT, Serverless, Data Streaming and Analytics, Modernization & Migration as well as Security.

Job Description

We are seeking a skilled Data Engineer to join our delivery team. You will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining data pipelines and data architectures to support data-driven decision making within our clients’ organization. You will work closely with Data Scientists, Data Analysts, and other stakeholders to identify and prioritize data needs, and you will be responsible for implementing scalable and reliable data pipelines, lakes and warehouses to support these needs.
Key responsibilities:
Design and build data pipelines and data architectures.
Collaborate with Data Scientists, Data Analysts, and other stakeholders to identify and prioritize data needs.
Ensure that data pipelines are scalable, maintainable, and reliable.
Troubleshoot and resolve data pipeline issues as needed.
Stay up-to-date with new technologies and best practices in data engineering, especially on AWS.
This is a hands-on role and will require a great deal of “can-do” attitude!
We have a hybrid office working model and like to occasionally meet the clients’ team at their offices.

Qualifications

We believe that you are open-minded to new ideas and flexible when meeting new challenges to succeed in this role. You have the ability to work independently and prioritize tasks effectively to deliver on time and with quality. You enjoy collaborating and are comfortable sharing your knowledge with your colleagues and clients.
Key requirements:
You have been working at least 3 years as a Data Engineer, building data pipelines, data lakes, and data warehouses.
Strong programming skills in Python and SQL. Java or Scala is a plus.
Good knowledge of data modeling with techniques/approaches like data vault, snowflake or star.
Experience in AWS services such as AWS Kinesis, AWS Glue, AWS S3, AWS Redshift, and AWS Athena
Experience with data mesh architecture is a plus
BS degree in a relevant field (e.g. Computer Science, Data Science, etc.) or equivalent work experience.
You are fluent in English in order to communicate with various stakeholders both technical and business oriented.

Additional Information

At Devoteam Stockholm you get:
Challenging and rewarding assignments; many of them end-to-end
Wellness grants for sports activities (5000 SEK/year)
Passionate and skilled colleagues
Human-centric and value-based culture
Variety of social events
About Devoteam A Cloud
Devoteam A Cloud is a Premier Partner to AWS with 4 competencies, 400+ AWS certified experts and 700+ certifications. In 2020, Devoteam A Cloud trained over 1000+ people.
At Devoteam, we deliver innovative technology consulting for businesses. As a pure player for Digital Transformation of large organizations across EMEA, our 10000+ professionals are dedicated to ensuring our clients win their digital battles. With a unique transformation DNA, we connect business and technology. Present in over 20 countries in Europe and the Middle East, and drawing on more than 20 years of experience, we shape Technology for People, so it creates value for our clients, for our partners and for our employees. Our mission is to build cultures of innovation at companies by transforming the way they work and by elevating their customer experiences.
We are looking for people with big ambitions, who want to grow with us and help companies build a culture of innovation with AWS solutions.
At Devoteam, we share our knowledge, learn from each other and from other experts by giving or listening to talks, participating in Hackathons, taking hands-on classes and getting certified.

A fair chance.
Devoteam is open to applications from all sections of society. We believe diverse teams help us make better products. We welcome all people regardless of age, gender, experience and background.
If you can see yourself in this role and feel you can bring value and a unique perspective to Devoteam, we encourage you to send us your application - even if you do not necessarily meet all the above requirements.
We apply continuous recruitment, so make sure to send in your application as soon as possible, given that Devoteam A Cloud’s recruitment process allows us to hire someone else before the last application day.

Title: Senior Data Scientist
Description:
Founded in 2018, Kreditz is already the market leader in PSD2-credit scoring products.
We use Open Banking/PSD2-technology to create our revolutionizing real-time credit scoring products, which are beloved by banks, financial institutions, iGaming companies and many more. Kreditz products enable consumers, and businesses, to gain financial inclusion, and financial opportunity where none would be available with traditional credit scoring systems.
Our long-term vision "One world, One score" translates into our everyday mission of financial inclusion, and financial opportunity, for everyone around the globe
– Everyone deserves a fair assessment.
Come join us on our impactful mission!

ABOUT THE POSITION
Thanks to 18 months of unbroken growth (+310% FY21 vs FY20) we are now looking to increase our analytics organization further with an awesome Data Science ‘magician’ eager to advance Kreditz revolutionizing products even further alongside a team of credit scoring experts, mathematicians and genuinely passionate colleagues.
We are currently entering an exciting phase (startup>scaleup) where we will expand our market presence further, from the Nordics to selected countries in Europe. Our clients range from some of Europe’s largest banks and iGaming companies to smaller, innovative businesses.
As a Senior Data Scientist at Kreditz, your playing field is data, vast amount of data. Our products and services are highly data driven, and to remain innovative you need to be confident in the analysis of both the known, and the unknown. Kreditz expects you to be able to analyze large internal and external data sets, make data driven conclusions, and evaluate your findings to optimize Kreditz algorithms and statistical models. This role is an important part of Kreditz growing analytics team, which is led by our CAO.
If you share the excitement to work with state-of-the-art technology within Open Banking/PSD2, and to deliver market leading solutions that make a positive impact on our society, all the while being part of a growth journey across the world – this is the right position for you!

WHAT CAN KREDITZ OFFER
One-way ticket to an amazing growth journey you will never forget – A journey where everyone in the team plays a central role for our company’s success
Fun-loving, passionate, and talented colleagues with whom to share small and big, company and personal, milestones and accomplishments
Humble corporate culture – we celebrate all wins, no matter the size, together
24/7 access to gym/sauna/sports center at our office PLUS additional wellness allowance

TASKS
Some of the tasks you will be performing, and lead, as a Senior Data Scientist at Kreditz:
Management and structuring of vast amounts of data
Analysis, interpretations and predictions of data
Transaction categorization and exploration (NLP, classification)
Optimization of Kreditz algorithms and statistical models
Support junior colleagues in their analytical work
Lead model development, follow-ups and performance evaluation
Model ownership, including development and implementation
Project lead in both client- and internal projects
Proactive data driven product development together with Product owner

WE ARE LOOKING FOR
A colleague who is analytical, structured and communicative. Someone who (like us) is up for the BIG challenge to disrupt traditional credit scoring systems via Open Banking/PSD2-technology. To be successful in this role, you must have a positive
“We can do it” mindset, along with an appreciation of working in a fast-paced growth company. You are comfortable in being independent in your daily work as well as acting with responsibility both towards your colleagues and clients.
Additionally, we believe that you have:
+5 yrs experience from financial services/tech/insurance/consulting or equivalent relevant experience
A relevant academic background (Engineering, Data/IT, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics)
Proven experience from DL/ML/NPL projects within relevant industry
The ability to take your analysis and models to production deployment
Confident in coding languages such as: Python, R and SQL
Very good communications skills in English (speech/writing), Swedish or other language skills is meritorious
Credit risk modeling from bank or financial institutions is meritorious
Experience from PSD2/Open Banking is meritorious

APPOINTMENT OF ROLE
Q4 2022
SCOPE
Full time, permanent employment (tillsvidareanställning)
SALARY
Fixed monthly salary
REPORTING
You will be reporting to the company's CAO
WORKPLACE
Our office is in Danderyd, Stockholm.
RECRUITMENT PROCESS
We interview candidates on an ongoing basis (ongoing selection)

CONTACT
Lorenzo Puccio, COO, lorenzo@kreditz.com
If you want to know more about the role, feel free to reach out to Magnus Källhager, Chief Analytics Officer, magnus@kreditz.com , +4670-7913984

Title: Knowledge graph consultant - Stockholm
Description:
Join our international community within knowledge graph technology, where you get to exchange experiences and knowledge with other knowledge graph experts within Capgemini.
We are Scandinavia's leading data, analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards a data-driven decisions.
What You’ll Do
As a Knowledge graph consultant, you will help our clients making better data-driven decisions by modeling and building robust data flows, creating an efficient data transporter, and building data architecture for Machine Learning solutions and BI solutions. You will also work with the development of computer science solutions stars on graph technology.
Our clients exploit all capabilities of the W3C Semantic Stack (RDF, RDFS, SPARQL, OWL, SHACL), graph databases and ontology modelling tools. While others focus more on tech stack like Neo4j, Cypher or Labeled Property Graph implementations.
We like to see that you have experience with some or several of above-mentioned technologies!
We also like to combine knowledge graphs with Natural Language Processing, meaning this might also be the perfect opportunity for someone with a background as linguist combined with a great interest in knowledge graphs.
You will be given the opportunity to work with a variation of clients located across Northern Europe. We work in a hybrid working model, meaning that, from time to time you might be asked to travel while on other occasions work remotely. To be successful in the role, we think that you thrive in an international environment, where you generously share your domain knowledge within Graph technology.
We hope that you enjoyed reading this job description and that this is exactly what you are looking for since you have a background within semantics, logic or linguistic.
We look forward to receiving your application!
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
Who You Are
You need to have:
Domain experience in knowledge graph technologies, you also enjoy solving complex modeling problems.
Knowledge about Linked Data Concepts
ETL processes with various graph databases.
Experience in Interaction with graph databases through standardized APIs and query languages
Information and Data Management
Curiosity and eagerness to learn new things
Programming skills (specific language is not required, but we use Python, Java or .Net)
Semantic technologies:
Utilize (W3C) Standards of the Semantic Stack
Knowledge regarding several datavases or excellent on at least one
Modelling knowledge with ontologies using various tools.
Skills for LPG
Knowledge regarding several databases or excellent on at least one.
It is not required, but an advantage if you also bring:
Architectural thinking
Data virtualization
Data mapping
Graph analysis
Graph visualization
Lifecycle Management of knowledge graphs in an enterprise environment
Skills for semantic technologies
Advanced reasoning and RDF validation
Skills for LPG
Machine Learning on Graphs

Title: BI expert
Description:
Nu letar vi på Knowit Experience efter dig som har erfarenhet av Data Science och Data Engineering. Jobbar du med dataanalys och datahantering, och känner dig redo för att bidra med insikter på en ny arbetsplats? Hos oss får du möjligheten att bygga upp ett team och hjälpa oss driva affären inom Data Science med riktigt härliga kollegor. Vi är redo. Är du?

Om rollen
Rollen kommer dels innebära uppdrag inom Data Science, dels att bygga upp ett team inom området. Detta tror vi att du kommer göra genom ett redan befintligt kontaktnät, men givetvis också med hjälp av dina kollegor. Med andra ord kommer du få stor möjlighet att växa och utvecklas i din roll.

Om dig
Du har jobbat med data science och data engineering de senaste åren, och känner dig redo för nästa steg. Du har kanske erfarenhet av eller är nyfiken på områden som AI och Machine Learning. Vidare har du genuin förståelse för databaser, vikten av och hur man jobbar med integrationer samt har erfarenhet av relevanta verktyg.

Det är meriterande om du har god förståelse för hur moderna molnplattformar och tjänster möjliggör processering av data från källsystem till färdig dataprodukt. Har du även jobbat med automatisering och datapipelines är det också ett plus.

Vi ser gärna att du har förståelse för konsultrollen, och triggas av att få vara med och bygga upp ett nytt erbjudande för våra kunder. Har du erfarenhet av att bolla behov och lösningar med kund och därmed driva upp nya affärer är du precis den vi söker.
Arbetsuppgifter som du kan komma att jobba med hos oss är allt från att modellera data till att bygga datalager och utveckla rapporter, och givetvis gillar du att sätta dig in i kundens behov och hjälpa dem se nya möjligheter.

Om oss
På Knowit vill vi inte bara att du ska utvecklas inom ditt kompetensområde, utan också som människa. Du har stora möjligheter att påverka din arbetssituation och ta initiativ till hur bolaget kan utvecklas och hur vi kan stötta våra kunder i deras utveckling. Vi drivs av en stark entreprenörsanda, som vi gärna ser att du vill vara med och utveckla framåt.
Vi är ett schysst bolag. Relationer är viktiga för oss och därför vill vi jobba tätt tillsammans i teamen och med våra kunder. Vi har kollektivavtal, förmånspaket och vi strävar efter att vara en sund och frisk arbetsplats. Du får givetvis massor av härliga och kompetenta kollegor och ett stort nätverk att samarbeta med.

Har du frågor om tjänsten?
Hör gärna av dig till: Linda Frostvik (teamchef) på 072-5343213, linda.frostvik@knowit.se

Title: AI Software Developer - Work in Sweden
Description:
Work in Sweden
All of our job offerings are temporarily remote from your home country, but then we will help you migrate to an amazing country, Sweden! We will provide you with a work permit and an exciting job opportunity.

About the Role
Our client development team focused on product development within Life Science and above all Medical Technology is looking for new colleagues! Innovation and growth are high on their agenda and right now there are great opportunities to be directly involved in exciting assignments in Gothenburg.

The purpose of the role is to work on Graph Data Science (GDS) library to implement machine learning algorithms on graphs. This can include leveraging known algorithms, adapting them, or designing novel methods. Identifying and integrating new areas of research and modeling that can solve even our customers’ most difficult problems.

Apply today! Get the job! Get a new life!
Requirements
Are you are a hands-on person, that loves coding as much as anything else and would like to deploy software engineering practice into machine learning projects? You probably have most of the following:
An experienced software developer (3+) with a strong mindset of building a scalable and high-quality software product.
Experience in machine learning, mathematics, and/or statistics
A great interest in big data and machine learning technology. Spark and Hadoop are good to have.
Experienced in one of the following programming languages: Python, Scala, or Java.
Hands-on experience in DevOps and automate software development process, like familiar with tools like Jenkins, Docker, and Kubernetes, etc.
Experienced in at least one of cloud solutions like AWS, Azure, or GCP
As a person, you are self-motivated, flexible and a good team player in an Agile team setup, willing to take different kinds of tasks.

About the Company
We are not offering just a new job. We want to help you to build a new exciting life in a country where technology and innovation are a reality in the present and the compass of the future. When you come to Sweden, you can count you will get a real work-life balance; you will delight and learn from the job challenges as working for companies that develop unique products and services; but also where you can be sure that your personal time is respected, so you can enjoy all the aspects of your personal life.

Sweden is well known for its secure and tranquil life, where personal differences are respected, and diversity is a common value, as the greatest egalitarian society in the world. So if you are a talented Software developer, this is your chance to live more than ever imagined.

Title: Senior Software and Analytics Engineer
Description:
Job Description Summary
We are looking for a Senior Software and Analytics Engineer in our Engineering & Technology organization. Arcam, a GE Additive company, is an innovative partner for manufacturing in the orthopedic implant and aerospace industries, where we deliver customer value through our competence and solution orientation. Since the birth of Arcam, our vision has remained the same: to revolutionize the art of manufacturing complex parts. Featuring some of the most advanced additive technologies available, machines from Arcam enable customers to grow products quickly and precisely.We design and manufacture state-of-the-art metal 3D printers. GE Additive is committed to creating a diverse environment and is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. Employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, religion, national or ethnic origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age or disability. We are not all the same. Just Be yourself @ GE Additive. #LI-MW
Job Description
You will work with focus on building sensor analytics into our machine software. The sensing and monitoring functions within Additive are rapidly evolving and the industry is constantly pushing for more machine surveillance and in-situ process monitoring. In our machines, there is a huge potential in utilizing signals emitted when the electron beam hits the metal. Smart signal processing can turn the sensor data (x-ray, NIR-cameras, spectrometers etc.) into valuable machine and melt process feedback.
We are looking for a person with an interest of exploring the unknown and passionate to develop sensing technology in our EBM machines. You will have a central role in how sensing technologies are developing and are merging into our products, using your software engineering expertise. The position will include occasional travelling a few times a year to partners around the world.
You will contribute with your great coding skills, knowledge of software design principles and full lifecycle development.
Arcam EBM is a part of a bigger GE Additive family and this role requires collaboration through-out the GE Additive software community. Advanced control software and monitoring software is an integral part of our metal 3D printer; you thrive when you work in cross-functional teams and help solve tough problems.
Responsibilities
Evaluate software solutions
Enable software capability improvements
Full lifecycle development
Serve as a subject matter expert on analytics and data science
Sensor data acquisition, analytics, and algorithm programming
Analyze and troubleshoot software related issues
Cooperate with other teams to deliver a suitable solution
Produce specifications and determine operational feasibility
Integrate software components into a fully functional software system
Your Profile
At least five years of experience in relevant industry or academia
Master’s degree in Mathematics, Physics, or Computer Engineering
Good knowledge in algorithms and sensor utilization
Track record of software development
Innovative, quality conscious and business-oriented person
You are a collaborative person, since you will be working together in a team with sensor/electronics specialists and software programmers
Broad technical knowledge is a plus
Good communication in verbal and written English. Fluent in Swedish is meriting.
Experience in object oriented language (C#, Java, C++, …)
We offer
A fun, flexible and technically advanced environment with interesting customers. Full time position with a wide variety of added employee benefits, including bonus, flexible working hours, health and pension insurance benefits. We offer you an exciting and global working environment which will give you valuable experience and contribute to your future development. You will have the opportunity to interact with highly committed colleagues from different cultures and within all engineering fields. You will work side by side with world leading experts.
We strive for gender balance and believe that actively prioritizing a high level of diversity in our workforce creates competitive advantage. It is our people that make the difference! #LI-MW
Additional Information
Relocation Assistance Provided: No
