Title: Engagement Manager
Description:
Combient Mix is hiring an Engagement Manager to manage customers and oversee the projects that propel our clients forwards in the transformational journey of reaping the benefits and realising business value from data.
As the Engagement Manager, you ensure high customer satisfaction in managing communication and agreed project deliveries in ongoing engagements. You consult our sales team in the pre-sales process in new business opportunities and in expansion of current customer engagements, providing insight of the customer needs and feasibility of proposed solutions.
By liaising with the Data Practice Managers who manage the internal teams at Mix, you ensure the right competences are assigned to your customer projects, and that they have the best conditions to deliver consistent and high-quality work.
To create the best conditions to deliver high-quality work, you make sure projects are kicked-off, followed-up on project goals and closed in a timely manner. When closed, you manage reviews and retrospectives, to bring learnings to new and existing customer projects.
Responsibilities
Participate in the pre-sales and preparation work for new projects.
Establish highly effective relationships with customers and other relevant internal stakeholders.
Allocate the team resources for current and upcoming projects. Work with Data Practice Managers to assess the competencies required to successfully carry out projects.
Ensure kick-off, review and closing of projects; ensuring project review and retrospectives are carried out and that learnings are implemented and acted on.
Identify, flag and resolve any project risks and blockers.
Manage and follow-up on customer needs, expectations and progress towards project goals.
Being the liaison between the customer and the internal consultants, supporting and managing consultant interaction at the customer site.
Support internal consultants in communication, prioritisation and progress, if necessary.
Work with Data Practice Managers to ensure the wellbeing of internal consultants within projects.
Who you are
Strong ability to effectively communicate and collaborate with customers, understanding their needs and proposing feasible solutions that will add value to the customers' needs.
Ability to provide business context, project goals and measures to the team of consultants assigned to the customer project.
Strong at building relationships and trust with teams and customer representatives.
Confident in applying multiple project management methodologies, adjusting to what best fits the various projects and customers.
Strong time-management skills with the ability to focus on priorities, manage expectations and deliver against agreed deadlines.
Solid qualifications and/ or understanding of Data Science, Machine Learning and Data Engineering, to be able to understand customer needs, assess feasibility and make proposals of solutions.
Experience from consultancy and customer facing businesses will be beneficial in this role.
Be confident in running workshops internally and with customer engagements.
Excellent verbal and written communication skills in English, Swedish or Finnish would also be beneficial in some of the customer contacts.
Location: Stockholm
Our work language is English.
Sounds interesting? Please get in touch and send your CV our way.

Title: Senior Analyst - Fraud Prevention
Description:
On our path to becoming the world’s favorite way to shop, we’re assembling an unparalleled global talent network, accelerating individual careers, and disrupting entire industries. We are on a mission to liberate humanity from all the meaningless time spent managing their purchases and finances, so they can do more of what they love. We’re in search of global talent eager to embrace our atmosphere and defy their own expectations.

We are looking for ambitious people with significant drive! We need problem solvers, initiative takers, people that see opportunities and potential to improve. You should be passionate about your job and enjoy a fast paced international working environment. You will play an important role in taking Klarna to the next level - thus, you should desire to go above and beyond to deliver and grow as an individual. At Klarna we embrace change, you should dare to challenge the status quo and be persistent in doing so.

Analytics at Klarna is divided into several teams with their unique responsibilities. One of these teams is our Fraud Analytics Team, which focuses on the continuous improvement of our fraud real-time decisioning for every transaction processed by Klarna. E-Commerce is changing quickly and so do the patterns of fraud. We are looking for a number of analysts at varying levels to join our team! Our Analysts aim to identify these patterns with the help of various tools to protect our business, merchants and consumers from any fraud related losses and risks.
What you will do
Use statistical analysis tools and techniques to develop automated fraud detection and real-time decisioning strategies
Collaborate with Data Scientists to build and implement fraud pattern models
Work with other teams across the business (particularly Engineering, Product and Commercial) to devise robust fraud strategies for new products and markets
Create, test and monitor new fraud tools and strategies from scratch
Work on proof of concepts involving new technologies and proactively seek out vendor and internal solutions to fraud problems
Ensure metrics and strategies are fit for purpose in terms of the current fraud environment and emerging threats
Work closely with the investigations team to understand threats and develop mitigations
Communicate and involve stakeholders to respond to any fraud related incidents as the first touchpoint for Legal, Finance, Engineering, Data Science and other partners
Who you are:
A degree from a university in a numerate subject (e.g. Economics, Science, Engineering, Mathematics)
Exceptional analytical thinking abilities, decision making and problem solving skills
Strong proficiency in SQL with the ability to analyze large quantities of data using statistical analysis tools such as Python or R
Experience in the entire Analytics lifecycle, from requirements gathering, data extraction, manipulation and analysis to sharing insights and advising on decision making
Good understanding and experience in visualization tools (e.g., QlikSense, Tableau)
Excellent track record in optimizing business performance and identifying gaps in business strategy, with a focus on financial services, ideally fraud
Working proficiency and communication skills in verbal and written English
Fantastic stakeholder management skills
Passion for learning about Fraud
How to apply

Send over a CV in English

Location: Stockholm, Sweden
Please note that we don't offer relocation assistance for this position.

What we offer:

Diversity & Community
With our diversity of skills, perspectives and backgrounds, we can create, innovate, and disrupt like no other. Diversity is part of who we are, and essential to our success.

Ownership & Impact
Here, every voice matters. We’re organized into hundreds of small teams, each run like a start-up, focused on their own problem-space.

Trust & Collaboration
Successes and failures are won together at Klarna in a melting pot of teams. Win, lose, and learn, we’re on this path together.

If you love what you do, you should love where you do it. We appreciate that everyone’s different and has their own preferences of where and how to work. We genuinely believe in the power of regular face-to-face interactions in building close connections with our teams, but we also strongly believe people can work effectively remotely. This means that combining both is the key to success.

At Klarna, You can choose between working from the office, remotely within your employment country, or even outside of it for up to 20 working days per year. Flex it up!

Challenges & Rewards
We take a very Swedish approach to benefits. Support for parents, health and wellness perks—we’ve got you covered.

About Klarna
Since 2005 Klarna has been on a mission to revolutionize the retail banking industry. With over 150 million global active users and 2 million transactions per day, Klarna is meeting the changing demands of consumers by saving them time and money while helping them be informed and in control. Over 450,000 global retail partners, including H&M, Saks, Sephora, Macys, IKEA, Expedia Group, and Nike have integrated Klarna's innovative technology to deliver a seamless shopping experience online and in-store. Klarna has over 6,000 employees and is active in 45 markets. For more information, visit Klarna.com

It is our commitment that every qualified person will be evaluated according to skills regardless of age, gender, identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability status or religion. Please refrain from including your picture and age with the application.

Title: Systemspecialist säkerhet
Description:
I skogen växer framtiden. Här hittar vi morgondagens lösningar för ett hållbart och biobaserat samhälle. Men vi hittar också en traditionell bransch i förändring. Vi på Södra-IT är på en förändringsresa driven av möjligheterna med avancerad dataanalys, mobila arbetssätt, agilitet och ett starkt kulturbyggande. Vår utgångspunkt är maximerat värdeskapande med hjälp av modern teknik.
Det är en resa där vi vågar bryta ny mark, göra fel och försöka igen. Vi som har klivit ombord tror starkt på kreativitet och delegering av ansvar till våra team för att de ska vara självgående i så stor utsträckning som möjligt med eget mandat. Vi arbetar med den absolut senaste tekniken och de skarpaste verktygen inom data science, cloud, devops, och automation och har ett väl utvecklat partnersamarbete med ledande leverantörer som utvecklas tillsammans med oss.
Södra Skogsägarna har en tydlig molnstrategi och har valt Microsoft Azure som plattform med Microsoft Dynamics på topp. Vi använder sedan länge Microsoft 365 för våra affärsdokument och kliver nu in i Dynamics 365 som affärsstödsystem. Övriga funktioner och servrar är sedan tidigare redan flyttade till Microsofts datacenter Azure.
Om arbetsuppgifterna:
Södra Skogsägarna söker nu en driven Systemspecialist med fokus på säkerhet till vår IT-avdelning i Växjö. Du kommer att ingå i ett starkt team som ansvarar för att säkerställa funktionaliteten av våra applikationer, servrar och nätverk, men även tjänster och funktioner i Azure och olika SaaS tjänster. I rollen blir du en viktig funktion för att säkerställa att vi har en IT-miljö som kan stå emot och hantera olika typer av cyber attacker.
I rollen ingår bland annat följande uppgifter:
Agera och följa upp på larm från våra centrala säkerhetssystem och åtgärda eventuella säkerhetsproblem.
Utveckla Södras IT avdelning med nya tekniker, system och processer för att förbättra den grundläggande säkerheten.
Delta och leverera i koncerngemensamma projekt som kräver stark kompetens inom infrastruktur och säkerhet.
Ansvara för att nya och befintliga system publiceras på ett effektivt och säkert sätt.
Dina erfarenheter
Som person är du målinriktad och driven i ditt arbete. Du är en problemlösare som på ett lugnt och metodiskt sätt planerar och strukturerar dina arbetsuppgifter och ansvarsområden. Vidare är du också kommunikativ och kan arbeta tillsammans med andra teammedlemmar och samarbetspartners på ett värdeskapande sätt där vi växer och utvecklas tillsammans.
Vi ser gärna att du som söker har några års erfarenhet av säkerhetsarbete inom infrastruktur. Gärna att du har arbetat med både serverrelaterade tjänster och nätverk. Har du även erfarenhet av arbete med F5 eller Cisco ser vi detta som positivt.
Mer konkret söker vi dig med erfarenhet av tex följande:
Microsoft Defender
Microsoft M365 och Azure säkerhetsportaler
Microsoft’s olika Azure tjänster
Checkpoint
Fortinet
Din arbetsgivare Södra
Södras gemensamma värdegrund är långsiktigt agerande och värdeskapande relationer. Medarbetare som trivs och visar ett stort engagemang är avgörande för vår framgång och utgör kärnan i vår verksamhet. För oss är en frisk och säker arbetsplats en central del av vårt kontinuerliga arbete med att utveckla våra medarbetares kompetens och yrkeskunnande. Vi vill att våra medarbetare ska må bra och erbjuder därför bland annat hälsoprofilbedömningar, friskvårdsbidrag och sjukförsäkring till våra anställda. Vår långsiktiga strävan är att Södras anställda ska spegla den mångfald som finns i befolkningen. Vi välkomnar sökanden med olika bakgrunder och ursprung.
Placering/Anställning
Tjänsten är placerad på Södras huvudkontor i Växjö och är en tillsvidareanställning på heltid.
Vill du veta mer? Vill du veta mer om rekryteringsprocessen är du välkommen att kontakta HR-direkt, 0470–89 500. För frågor gällande verksamheten vänligen kontanta Magnus Linnér, Head of IT Platform,+46725834758.
Fackliga frågor hänvisas till:
Fredrik Dacke, SACO, 0470-855 02
Teddy Hedlund, Unionen, 0470-595 61
Ansök via länken nedan senast den 11:e december. Vi kommer att påbörja urvalet efter att ansökningstiden har gått ut.

Title: Connect with us for future jobs in software development at Storykit!
Description:
Founded in 2018 in Stockholm, we are expanding the universe of video content creators from hundreds of thousands of video editors, to hundreds of millions of storytellers world wide, who can now create video.
We are the complete video creator busy changing how the world thinks about and works with video.
Storykit is constantly growing! At the moment we are not actively recruiting but you are welcome to amaze us with your application for future opportunities in both employment, ex job (thesis) and summer jobs. Please clarify in your application what type of employment you are looking for!
How you will make life easier for hundreds of millions of storytellers worldwide:
At Storykit we have a broad range of roles within the tech area, so depending on your ambitions and skillsets we can see opportunities to work with fullstack development, or as a specialist with focus on either frontend, backend or video engineering.
You will be part of our ever-evolving team of developers, sometimes spending months designing and implementing new exciting features for our customers. And then mixing that up with investigating edge cases for customers or optimizing performance.
(Please note that we are not actively recruiting through this ad and therefore the response time may vary. We will get back to you as soon as possible and when we find an interesting opportunity!)

What about the tech?
We're developing the front end of our web application in Angular 12 with TypeScript and NGXS.
Our backend runs in a NodeJS runtime environment with microservices architecture. It's hosted on Heroku and AWS with GitHub Actions for CI/CD. We develop all new features in TypeScript, while some old features are still in JavaScript (we're continuously rebuilding those using TS). On the database side, we're using MongoDB with Mongoose as ORM. However, we also use PostgreSQL for our Data/AI solutions.
Additionally, we develop one part of our rendering cluster in Rust + Kubernetes.
Please note that we don't expect you to have experience working with all the tech we use, instead we hope you want to grow in your role with us!

What about the team?
Glad you asked! Team spirit and collaboration are super important for us and currently, we're around two dozen developers working together to make our product great.
We're divided into three functional teams that have full-stack competence, hence they are responsible for everything from designing the feature to implementing and testing their code. We manage our projects using a mix of Scrum and Kanban.
Video - handle all parts of our rendering cluster as well as new slide types/layouts
Data/AI - create features that automatically recommend video content for our users (layouts, text, music, stock images/videos from our library, etc.)
Organize - are responsible for developing Video Studio (our video editing application) and the Creative part of our tool. This includes functionality for handling accounts, user data, different accesses, etc.

We also have a cross-team that includes functions that work with several teams (such as DevOps, UI/UX, CTO, Engineering Manager) and one UI Engineer that works mainly with our website storykit.io.

What can you expect from us?
At Storykit, you can expect a safe and open-minded environment that is both challenging and ambitious. We are growing tremendously fast and therefore give all employees a lot of responsibility from day one.
We set high goals, but also make sure that everyone has the right support to be able to reach them. Due to our fast growth, there are almost endless opportunities for development in the organization. You will work in an awesome team, and with generous terms & conditions.

Who are we looking for - really?
We're looking for developers with various seniority levels and experiences who want to connect with us for future possibilities at Storykit (and who wants to focus on either backend, frontend, full stack or video/rendering).
To be a good match, we believe that you:
Have a degree within a MSc or BSc in Media Technology, Computer Science, Systems Engineering or similar. If you're looking for a thesis job, it can potentially be in our interest as well
Have some experience working with TypeScript/JavaScript or Rust (either via work, school projects or in personal projects)
Are comfortable communicating in English
Are authorized to live and work in Sweden (via work permit, EU citizenship, permanent residency or similar)
Bonus
Experience in Angular 2+ and NodeJS
Furthermore, you generally have a strong belief about using the right kind of tool for the right problem and are skeptically curious about new frameworks, libraries, and programming languages

Join the fun!
Storykit is a hybrid remote company, and as a member of our team, you would work either full-time or part-time from our HQ in central Stockholm (we have a very flexible hybrid work policy).
We hope you’re up for the challenge and look forward to hearing more about you - submit your application today. Since this is a way to connect with us for future job openings it can take a little bit longer before you hear from us but please stay put :)

Buzz: JavaScript, JS, TypeScript, Nodejs, Node, Node.js, Angular, React, AWS, Amazon Web Services, Heroku, Backend Developer, Backend Engineer, Backend Software Developer, Frontend developer, Frontend Engineer, Software Engineer, Fullstack Developer, Full stack Engineer, Full-stack Software Engineer, MongoDB, AI, ML, Artificial intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Engineer, Data Science

Department
Tech
Locations
Stockholm
Remote status
Hybrid Remote

Title: Är det dags för dig att bli ledare? Drivs du av digitalisering och teknik? Bli vår nya gruppchef i Stockholm!
Description:
Vill du ha ett jobb som gör skillnad och en arbetsgivare som har hållbarhet i fokus? Då är du välkommen till Sweco! Den framtid som kan kännas avlägsen i resten av samhället är i högsta grad närvarande hos oss. Att ligga steget före är vårt jobb.
Triggas du av att:
Skapa och driva affärer inom IT för samhällsbyggnadsbranschen?
Bygga och leda en konsultgrupp med specialister inom IT, digitalisering och systemutveckling, med fokus på data science, data engineering, IoT och BI?
Coacha och utveckla medarbetare till att bli de bästa på marknaden samtidigt som de har riktigt roligt på jobbet?
Då vill vi ha dig som gruppchef!

Varför jobba hos oss?
Ett av våra allra viktigaste fokusområden de närmaste åren är den ökade digitaliseringen och behovet av smarta och effektiva tekniska lösningar för utformningen av morgondagens hållbara städer och samhällen. Våra tjänster inom IT för samhällsutveckling är starkt efterfrågade på en snabbt växande marknad. Vårt syfte är att göra samhället smartare.
Du kommer att representera ett starkt varumärke med en bred kund- och uppdragsportfölj. Våra kunder finns över hela Sverige och är inom både offentlig och privat sektor. På Sweco värdesätter vi ett gott affärsmässigt förhållningssätt då våra kontaktytor bygger på långa samarbeten och goda relationer. Hos oss får alla också lov att skapa affärer.
Vi vågar påstå att vi är en av Sveriges mest attraktiva arbetsgivare. Vi erbjuder en omväxlande och dynamisk arbetsmiljö med stora möjligheter till personlig utveckling. Sweco erbjuder utbildningar inom bland annat teknik och ledarskap bl.a. via vår egen akademi. Att känna arbetsglädje och ha kul på jobbet är något vi värdesätter högt.
Din framtida roll
Som gruppchef på Sweco kommer du i kombination med din chefsroll även vara med och leverera som expert/konsult en mindre andel av din tid. Du kommer på sikt att ansvara för en grupp, om 10-15 personer, som du får vara med att bygga upp från grunden. Du ingår också i regionledningen, där du tillsammans med övriga gruppchefer och regionchef delar ansvaret att driva och utveckla verksamheten framåt. Du kommer att vara ansvarig för att växa vår affär på den lokala marknaden.
Vi genomför just nu en satsning på att öka vårt erbjudande inom data science, data engineering, IoT-lösningar och BI, din roll kommer innefatta att växa en grupp inom nämnda områden.
På Sweco är det viktigt med jämställdhet och vi strävar alltid efter en jämn könsfördelning, vilket du i din roll kan bidra till genom kompetensbaserad och fördomsmedveten rekrytering. Idag är fördelningen ca 35% kvinnor och 65% män på regionen.
Rollen som gruppchef kommer innefatta:
Utveckling av affärer, tjänster och kundrelationer.
Personalansvar för dina konsulter.
Ansvar för att attrahera och rekrytera nya medarbetare till teamet.
Budget- och resultatansvar.
Ledarskapet
Varför jobba med mig?
”Som ledare är jag lugn, trygg, lyhörd och strukturerad. Jag drivs av förbättring, effektivisering samt att nå uppsatta mål. Jag tror på teamwork och mitt ledarskap är inkluderande. Vi jobbar nära varandra i regionledningen och som din närmaste chef kommer jag att stötta dig och din utveckling. Min roll är att se till så att regionen mår och går så bra som möjligt.”
Andreas Larsdalen, Regionchef
Dina erfarenheter
Vi söker dig som:
Tycker om och är duktig på att skapa affärer.
Har konsulterfarenhet samt kompetens inom systemutveckling och/eller IT.
Har ledarerfarenhet, exempelvis som projektledare, teamlead eller förvaltningsledare. Dock inget krav på tidigare personalansvar.
kommunicerar obehindrat på svenska och engelska.
För att trivas i rollen så bör du vara orädd, ansvarstagande, driftig, engagerad och kunna hantera en ofta varierad arbetsvardag med en hög förmåga att kunna prioritera.
Ansökan
Annonsen kommer att ligga ute till och med 2023-01-31. Intervjuer sker löpande och tjänsten kan tillsättas före sista ansökningsdatum. Vi tar inte emot ansökningar via mejl, utan hänvisar samtliga ansökningar till ansökningsformuläret nedan.
Vi ber om överseende att det under julledigheterna kan dröja en tid innan du får återkoppling.
Vi återkopplar till samtliga sökande efter avslutad rekryteringsprocess.
Varmt välkommen med din ansökan!
Kontakta oss
Vill du höra mer om tjänsten? Välkommen att kontakta
Andreas Larsdalen, Regionchef
073-412 64 69
andreas.larsdalen@sweco.se

Title: Principal Machine Learning Engineer | AI Center of Excellence
Description:
Craft:
Technology & Development
Job Description:
Principal Machine Learning Engineer | AI Center of Excellence
This role is available in either of our sweet locations in:
London
Stockholm
Do you have a dynamic approach to solving problems and processing data at scale? Are you passionate about building machine learning (ML) tools for data scientists? Do you believe machine learning (ML) can have a material impact on how we do business and want to be a part of the journey to help teams, company- wide, enhance our players’ experiences? Then you could be our new, shiny, Principal ML Engineer!
Your role within our Kingdom
You´ll be part of the AI Center of Excellence (ACE) team at King, working closely together with ML Engineers, ML Research Engineers and Data Scientists. Our mission? Discover potential ML use cases across the company, build data models & pipelines, ML models & infrastructure, provide ML use case services to our games reliably and at scale.
As ML Engineer at King, you will be using the latest technologies to build ML products that democratize ML model training, tuning and deployment across the company. With over 250+ million monthly active users and 50 billion events being uploaded daily, it’s key that you care about writing highly optimized code and care about quality. You’ll be working with both streaming as well as batch data in a highly challenging technical environment.
You will work in collaboration with business stakeholders, both within your team and supporting other teams, on creating value from data. Together with your team members you´ll get to learn on the job every day!
Skills to create thrills
So what about you? You have hands- on experience in various ML projects working as an experienced ML engineer. You are a strong advocate for best practices in ML solutions and you have good intuition on what ML models might be most effective and efficient. You are a technical leader, meaning you will be responsible for developing and evolving the solutions fitting the use cases.
Minimum Requirements:
MS or PhD in Computer Science/Engineering, Machine Learning, Data Science, Physics, Mathematics, or other engineering/scientific areas with 5+ years of experience.
Extensive experience working in applied AI/ML and Data Science projects
Deep knowledge and extensive experience with data science and machine learning concepts and algorithms
Experience in distributed data processing and modeling (batch & streaming)
Experience building data pipelines and ML pipelines
Experience in GCP data products (BigQuery, Cloud Storage, Dataflow, Pub/Sub to name a few)
Must be a tenacious and self- catalyzing problem solver. Must be able to synthesize disparate data, detect and work around broken data, and investigate every possibility until you are confident you have and understand a thorough solution
Process- oriented driving toward visibility, accountability, and communication
Team- oriented, ability to build long- lasting and collaborative relationships effectively. You work selflessly and enthusiastically, serving as a positive catalyst for collaborative solutioning
You contribute to the expertise in every data and analytic conversation as well as you listen with openness to other’s expertise
A passion for analytics and diving into as well as experiencing the products on which you work (video game enthusiasm with a solid understanding of the connection of gameplay to spending behavior is a plus)
Ability to adapt quickly, high tolerance for ambiguity, and ability to coordinate on a team
Tasty bonus skills
Have any sweet experience with one or some of the following areas? Then we sure like to hear about them!
Development in or exposure to environments/software products in Python and Java
Experience working with Tensorflow, Pytorch, Flink, Kafka, Spark or similar
Contributions to open source projects
We know that you are into games on some level (casual, console, board- games, Uno etc.)
Buzz: Data Modeling, Programmer, ML Engineer, Gaming, GCP, Platforms, AI, ML, TDD, Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Research and development, Data Science
About King
King is the game developer behind the world- famous Candy Crush franchise, as well as mobile game hits including Farm Heroes, Bubble Witch and Pet Rescue. Candy Crush is the top- grossing franchise in US app stores, a position it has held for the last two years, and King’s games are being played by 245 million monthly active users as of Q3 2021. King, which is part of the Activision Blizzard group since its acquisition in 2016, employs nearly 2,000 people in game studios in Stockholm, Malmö, London, Barcelona and Berlin, and offices in San Francisco, New York, and Malta.
A Great Saga Needs All Sorts of Heroes
Making games is fun. Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply cannot expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes.
Making the World Playful
Making the World Playful is what inspires us to create new experiences and raise the bar. It’s what makes King a place where we can all dream bigger, continue to add innovation to our games, broadening the portfolio and exploring new territories in mid- core and casual. We take the art and science of gaming to the next level through our curiosity for the unexplored, passion for games, respect for each other and love for our players - and we’re not afraid to have fun along the way. In fact, together with our parent company Activision Blizzard and experts around the world, we believe having fun is good for you. There has never been a better time to join us. We're dreaming bigger and see a world of possibilities ahead. If you share our passion, our values, and our hunger to shape the future, join us in Making the World Playful!
Applications need to be in English.
Discover King at careers.king.com

Title: Data Engineer to Hybrid Intelligence - a part of Capgemini Engineering
Description:
Are you looking for an R&D environment where you can work with world-class scientists and engineers on cutting edge projects? Do you want to contribute to a better world while building a career? Do you also have a passion for science, engineering, technology, business, data and human creativity?
Welcome to the World of Hybrid Intelligence.
Using a combination of deep domain knowledge within the R&D space supported by technical expertise, data science, analytics and software engineering, we work with our clients to find new ways to unlock the value held within their data, enabling better-informed business decisions.
Our work includes some of the most exciting and ambitious projects of our time. These projects make the world a better place: increasing productivity in the development of new medicines; designing satellites to observe and understand our universe; harnessing fusion power to provide unlimited, clean energy; minimizing risk for workers in harsh and dangerous conditions and much more.
We are now looking for Data Engineers to our Scandinavian Team
You will be part of a diverse and inclusive team of data scientists and engineers working on solving interesting, real-world problems that truly make a difference. Supported by our global knowledge base and network of skilled colleagues, augmented by ongoing professional development and training, you will be driving our technical solutions within Scandinavia. You will define routes to effective solutions, be able to present these to our clients, and then execute them through your team.
Learn more about what working at Capgemini Engineering is about here: https://capgemini-engineering....
To succeed in this role
During your career at Hybrid Intelligence, you will learn and have opportunities to develop your skills, but before you join us, you should have:
A Bachelor, Masters or PhD in science, computer science, mathematics, or engineering (STEM)
Academic or professional experience within data engineering, an analytical mindset, a willingness to roll up your sleeves and solve hands-on technical challenges
A minimum of 3 years of relevant data engineering experience
Experience in one or several object-oriented scripting languages: Python, Java, C++, Scala, etc.
Working knowledge of databases, SQL and/or Elasticsearch, and experience with data management tools such as Databricks.
Experience implementing data pipelines using tools such as Spark SQL, PySpark, Kafka and Hadoop.
Knowledge of cloud platforms, tools and services provided by AWS, Azure or Google Cloud
Understanding how to implement effective ETL steps on said platforms
Domain knowledge in life science, automotive, or consumer products is a plus
Excellent communication and presentation skills and an ability to explain complex concepts
Professional level ability in English – very strong plus if you’re Swedish speaking
Business analysis and tech project management skills are an advantage
Location
We are working closely with our client base in Gothenburg and the general west coast of Sweden. Having your residence in Gothenburg or nearby is a plus but not a must.
Application and contact
Selection and interviews are running instantaneously as the start is immediate. We look forward to your application!

Title: Test Manager
Description:
About this opportunity

Do you search for a new job opportunity to work in the forefront of the digitalization field, working with the latest technology and apply your DevOps, Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) skills to evolve product development? Then you might have found the perfect match here.

We are looking for two new graduate engineers to join our team, responsible for Test Management for Ericsson's 4G and 5G Radio Access Network products. You will contribute to evolve a data driven test management by evolving our test management landscape with AI and ML based solutions using a wide variety of both inhouse and open source technologies and tools. You will support the testers and test managers with DevOps, Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning techniques, solutions, tools and processes designed to achieve the optimal product quality, flow and cost efficiency. We organize in teams in which Lean and Agile way of working, customer focus, continuous improvement, innovation and knowledge sharing is part of the daily work

What you will do:

Develop competence in agile product development, and clarify requirements needed on test methodologies, tools within test management area
Evolve test avoidance, risk based testing and fast utilization of customer feedback
Model the big data in test in order to develop requirements on test data, test data infrastructure, test architecture, test management tools and processes
Explore where we can use AI and Machine Learning to automate processing the test data in order to optimize test coverage, flow and cost more efficiently
Develop DevOps thinking, explore where AI and ML techniques can evolve our Continuous Integration and Delivery Machine that is used to test and deliver our SW to the customer fast with high quality

You will bring:

MSc or PhD in Computer Science, Computer or Electrical Engineering
Deep knowledge and experience of DevOps, artificial intelligence, machine learning and modelling
Deep knowledge of data engineering and data science
Solid programming and scripting skills, including Unix, Linux and Python
Experience in some of the data technologies such as; Kafka, Mesos, Ceph, Spark, Postgres/ Cockroach, Elasticsearch, Linux
Solid understanding of cloud native product development
Solid understanding of cloud and virtualization technologies
Experience with containers, such as Docker or Kubernetes
Broad knowledge and interest in telecommunications, data technology, and automation areas
Solid understanding of software release and deployment and CI/CD pipelines
Digital citizen; likes using digital tools in managing work
Understanding of what is takes to be agile, without overhyping about it
Positive attitude to learn and grow
Has a “can do” attitude in facing challenges and ambiguity
Innovation mentality, curious, outspoken and polite personality
Fluent communicator, a hardworking presenter and conversation starter
Able to capture the big picture while paying attention to details
Exemplary time manager
Team player with right collaboration skills

Why join Ericsson?

At Ericsson, you´ll have an outstanding opportunity. The chance to use your skills and imagination to push the boundaries of what´s possible. To build never seen before solutions to some of the world’s toughest problems. You´ll be challenged, but you won’t be alone. You´ll be joining a team of diverse innovators, all driven to go beyond the status quo to craft what comes next.

Encouraging a diverse and inclusive organization is core to our values at Ericsson, that's why we nurture it in everything we do. We truly believe that by collaborating with people with different experiences we drive innovation, which is essential for our future growth. Title: E-mobility Engineer
Description:
I am Peter, your potential next leader. I know a lot about cows, not because I have a double degree in Data Science and applied mathematics but because I have worked 17 years with robots and milk production at DeLaval. So a couple of years ago, I thought to myself, what is beyond robots, cows, and milk? And I found my way in consultancy, and now I'm stuck in the world of exploring new things! My team at Knightec and I get the opportunity to create products needed in the market designed to be sustainable for customers who value our competence. Right now, I'm focusing and working with Electrification. I'm too humble to say that I'm an expert, but I have great experience in the field! I love the technical aspects of my work, creating, modifying, and developing products. But the best part of my day is to discuss, learn and mentor my team members to have the best chance to find their following context or projects. I appreciate open dialogues and transparency to give you situational leadership; that is one thing I can promise you!

Why working as a consultant will fit you
Because you want to focus on solving technical problems without internal politics, you want to make new products that last, not handling the old legacy. And you want to have a team with engineers who understand the problem you meet and help you see them from another perspective.
What will you work with?
For the transportation sector, electrification is the paradigm shift of the century. As an engineer within e-Mobility at Knightec, you could drive the change.
The required areas of expertise within electromobility cover a broad spectrum, and where you want to contribute is up to you. Whether you are skilled in Systems engineering, Embedded software development, Control systems design, or Test and verification, your knowledge will be valuable.
We believe that a holistic approach is required to make products and services succeed both now and in the future. Our way of working is in cross-functional teams closely collaborating with our customers.
What you need to bring
Our best guess is that you have an educational background in mechatronics, electronics, computer science, or software engineering with an interest in electrification and/or the automotive industry.
Electrification consist of a variety of building blocks, and we think you have competence and experience from one or several of the following:
Electric motors
Inverters
Battery technology
Battery Management Systems
Charging
More specifically, we are looking for skilled people whose key competencies lie within any of the following fields:
Systems Engineering
Embedded software development (Matlab Simulink, C, C++)
Electronics design
Control systems design
Test and Verification
Knightec
We are consultants in technology, digitalization, and leadership. We work to improve people's lives through game-changing solutions. We are engineers focusing on product development that should be sustainable and durable in edge technology in both in-house projects and at customer sites. We are more than 900 engineers in 10 different cities. To be a consultant at Knightec isn't just a job; it is the way to build a career that you can be proud of!

Title: Svenska kraftnät söker IT-jurist
Description:
Vill du också arbeta i en utvecklande miljö där du blir en avgörande länk i en samhällsviktig verksamhet? Med avancerad teknik och en stark vilja att hitta lösningarna genom hela IT-kedjan, från infrastruktur till data science, AI och machine learning, är Svenska kraftnät redo att anta de utmaningar som elektrifiering och energiomställning innebär. Vi söker nu dig som vill arbeta i en spännande roll hos oss som verksjurist med inriktning It-rätt.
Dina arbetsuppgifter
Den juridiska regleringen av IT-systemen utgör en hörnsten i arbetet med elektrifiering och energiomställning. I arbetet som jurist innebär det konkret att utveckla morgondagens IT-juridik i en dynamisk och högteknologisk miljö med internationell koppling och de mest avancerade tekniska systemen.
Två verksjurister arbetar i dag med IT-rätt, inbegripet dataskyddsfrågor och rättsliga frågor kopplat till cybersäkerhet på verket. Vi vill nu stärka upp med ytterligare en kvalificerad verksjurist med inriktning mot IT-rätt. Rollen innefattar att ge stöd inom:
den affärsjuridiska regleringen av Svenska kraftnäts IT-system och löpande affärsjuridiska frågor,
den juridiska regleringen av Svenska kraftnäts IT-säkerhet samt nationell säkerhet i Svenska kraftnäts digitala miljöer,
den juridiska regleringen av Svenska kraftnäts behandlingar av personuppgifter samt löpande dataskyddsfrågor.
Arbetet kan även komma att omfatta andra rättsområden, bl.a. förvaltningsrätt, upphandlingsrätt och EU-rätt samt IPR-frågor. Tjänsten är placerad på vårt huvudkontor i Sundbyberg.
Din bakgrund
Du ska ha en fullgjord juristexamen, vidare har du:
Några års erfarenhet av relevant juridiskt arbete från domstol, kommun, statlig myndighet, advokatbyrå, organisation eller företag,
Erfarenhet av IT-rättsligt arbete eller motsvarande erfarenhet som Svenska kraftnät bedömer likvärdig,
Mycket goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska i både tal och skrift.
Vi ser gärna att du även har:
En eftergymnasial utbildning inom IT-rätt (affärsjuridik med inriktning mot IT-rätt eller dataskydd/GDPR),
Erfarenhet av att hantera personuppgiftsincidenter och/eller tillsyn från Integritetsskyddsmyndigheten
Erfarenhet av avtalsrätt,
Erfarenhet av arbete med OSL-frågor, eller
Erfarenhet av cyber security.
Dina personliga egenskaper
För att trivas i rollen ser vi att du har en god samarbetsförmåga och tycker om att arbeta med andra då du kommer att ha många kontaktytor både inom och utanför myndigheten. Du är självgående och tar ansvar för dina arbetsuppgifter och kan själv driva dina frågor framåt. I rollen är det också viktigt att du har hög integritet, ett gott omdöme samt är lösningsorienterad och därmed har förmågan att hitta lämpliga lösningar för de frågor som uppstår i verksamheten. Detta särskilt då vi på flera sätt bryter ny mark inom IT-juridikens område.
Vi lägger stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper.
Vill du veta mer?
I denna rekrytering samarbetar vi med FAIRPLACE, har du frågor rörande tjänsten är du varmt välkommen att kontakta Anna Lensmar-Friedman, tel. nr. 076-000 25 55, anna.lensmar-friedman@fairplace.se Kontakta gärna rekryterande chef Li Axrup, li.axrup@svk.se. Fackliga representanter är Emma Thornberg, SACO, tel. 010 475 84 77 och Mikael Wallin, ST, tel. 010-475 84 94. Du når oss också via e-post: fornamn.efternamn@svk.se.
Sista ansökningsdag
Sista ansökningsdag är 28 februari 2023. Vi behandlar ansökningar löpande så vi välkomnar din ansökan så snart som möjligt.
Vårt erbjudande till dig
På Svenska kraftnät händer det mycket - vi är en organisation i förändring. Enligt Nyckeltalsinstitutets mätning Arbetsgivarindex är Svenska kraftnät en av elbranschens bästa arbetsgivare och arbetar utifrån ett personligt ledarskap. Du erbjuds god möjlighet till balans mellan arbete och privatliv, goda förmåner och mycket mer.
Som medarbetare hos oss blir du en del i en samhällsviktig organisation där vi värdesätter och strävar efter hög kollektiv intelligens. Det är med samarbete och effektivitet som vi ska uppnå vår vision "Säker elförsörjning för en hållbar samhällsutveckling". Svenska kraftnät arbetar för att främja mångfald och motverka diskriminering och ser gärna sökanden med olika bakgrund och erfarenheter till våra rekryteringar.
Då vi arbetar med samhällsviktig verksamhet är anställningen säkerhetsklassad och svenskt medborgarskap krävs. Säkerhetsprövning med registerkontroll kommer att genomföras före anställning. Med anställning följer en skyldighet att krigsplaceras.

Title: Associate Director, Medical and Payer Evidence Statistics
Description:
At AstraZeneca we turn ideas into life changing medicines. We’re focused on the potential of science to address the unmet needs of patients around the world. We commit to those areas where we think we can change the course of medicine and bring new ideas to life.
The Real-World Science & Digital team is a group within AstraZeneca’s global Evidence function which is driving the scientific use of Real-World Data to accelerate the way patients access innovative medicines. The Real-World Science and Digital team comprises of a group of statisticians, a data science group, Digital Platform leads and Data Strategy experts providing AstraZeneca with an enterprise hub for Real World Science.
It’s our vision to enhance human life by serving as a trusted source of expertise in statistical analysis methodology with a focus on medical research, promotion of the use of sound quantitative methods and strategic innovation in the generation of Real-World Evidence. Do you want to join us on our journey?
We are looking for an Associate Director to join our Medical and Payer Evidence Statistics (MPES) team at our site in Gothenburg, Sweden
What we do
MPES is a global team that shares a passion for statistics in observational research.
MPES Deliver/Implement statistical support to studies utilizing primary observational data and data from EMR, claims required by Therapeutic Area (TA) RWE strategies
MPES serves as group of expert reviewers of evidence analyses & analysis support (network) meta-analyses, matching adjusted indirect comparisons (MAIC), simulated treatment comparisons (STC), ML-NMR and beyond. We give health technology assessment (HTA) support in terms ofcost-effectiveness model verification and validation.
MPES supports the Medical and Payer Evidence Book of Work with 100+ studies per year and co-develops study designs, protocols, statistical analysis plans and clinical study reports.
Our team works with leading internal and external experts and provides general scientific and statistical external and internal consultancy.
With us you have many opportunities to grow your skills and expertise. We offer a range of trainings, both internal and external, and we encourage you to actively present at international meetings and at congresses as well as co-author scientific papers and reports.
What you’ll do
With your statistical expertise you provide input to the design, analysis and interpretation of observational studies and support the review of all analytical activities outsourced to external vendors.
The ideal candidate for the current role will be a curious, self-learner and will bring a proven track record of working with statistics and delivering value from observational studies or routinely collected data from healthcare settings in a range of contexts including Public Health, Pharmaceutical Research and Development and Commercial/ Payer and Patient Safety.
Essential for the role
Graduate degree in Statistics, Biostatistics, or related quantitative fields (epidemiology, health outcomes, health informatics or health economics) or equivalent course work/ technical experience with experience in pharma/healthcare or other relevant discipline.
Attention to detail, especially in reviewing voluminous data files
Thorough knowledge of statistical analysis and study design especially for observational studies
Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively on cross-functional teams across global & functional boundaries, both internally and externally.
Self-motivated with the ability to work independently to solve complex and challenging problems which may involve innovative strategies while maintaining focus on quality.
Excellent communication skills and ability to build strong relationships.
Strong project management/organizational, prioritization and multitasking skills.
The successful candidate is a team player with a desire to synergize within a collaborative culture that embraces curiosity and humility.
So, what’s next?
Join a talented and agile team that focus on what really matters. We’re inspired by the direct link between what we do, how this helps to accelerate the business and, ultimately, how this benefits peoples’ lives across the world.
Are you already imagining yourself joining us? Great! We can’t wait to hear from you!
Welcome with your application. Applications are reviewed on a rolling basis. Be the first to act!
Why AstraZeneca Gothenburg?
Our Gothenburg site is one of AstraZeneca's global centers. Collaboration comes in all forms - across teams, functions, countries and companies. The MPES group director is based in Sweden as well.

Title: Product Manager | Candy Crush Saga - In App Purchases & Economy
Description:
Craft:
Data, Analytics & Strategy
Job Description:
We are looking for a passionate and creative Product Manager interested in pushing our understanding and the performance of our in- app purchases as a part of the IAP & Economy- business unit in Candy Crush Saga.
You will get the opportunity to be part of an excellent team, where we innovate on an industry leading and genre defining game with over 200 million active players!
Your role within the Kingdom
As a Product Manager in the In App Purchase and Economy Area of Candy Crush Saga, you will be working with varied partners in a lively, dynamic and fast- paced environment. You’ll help us to develop new features and experiences to delight our players and grow our business.
Key responsibilities include:
Drive the product strategy and roadmap working closely with Engineering and other cross- functional colleagues such as UX Design, Game Design, Data Science, UX Research, Marketing, etc.
Oversee the implementation and execution of the product strategy, ensuring timely delivery of features and improvements whilst maintaining a high level of quality
Build a great team environment, coordinating and aligning your cross- functional team(s) towards our goals
Define and evaluate key results and performance metrics that inform the success of our products and features.
Use analytics and quantitative analysis to monitor game performance, recommend A/B- test optimizations and provide input for features to increase user retention, engagement, and monetization.
Provide stakeholders with regular or ad- hoc updates on the performance of the product/features
Skills to create thrills
You are a passionate problem solver and have the ability to draw data driven business insights that will add real value to King.
You are an excellent communicator with experience managing a variety of different stakeholders.
You are proactive and demonstrate the desire to learn quickly and work in a fast paced and collaborative environment whilst communicating effectively with teams and individuals across King.
Experience and capabilities that would suit this role:
You have experience in a product leadership or product management role at a tech/games company
Prior experience in an industry with very short implementation cycles such as digital products and services or games
Highly analytical, an excellent understanding of data and statistics, with the ability to interpret data with confidence and drive through your recommendations
Curiosity and willingness to learn new skills
About King
King is the game developer behind the world- famous Candy Crush franchise, as well as mobile game hits including Farm Heroes, Bubble Witch and Pet Rescue. Candy Crush is the top- grossing franchise in US app stores, a position it has held for the last two years, and King’s games are being played by 245 million monthly active users as of Q3 2021. King, which is part of the Activision Blizzard group since its acquisition in 2016, employs nearly 2,000 people in game studios in Stockholm, Malmö, London, Barcelona and Berlin, and offices in San Francisco, New York, and Malta.
A Great Saga Needs All Sorts of Heroes
Making games is fun. Especially when you do it with people who share the same idea of what makes a good workplace great. We design games for everyone, no matter where they are or who they are, and we employ all sorts of people from all kinds of backgrounds to bring them to life. Truth is, we simply cannot expect diversity in our players and originality in our games without first nurturing it in our people. A great saga needs all sorts of heroes.
Making the World Playful
Making the World Playful is what inspires us to create new experiences and raise the bar. It’s what makes King a place where we can all dream bigger, continue to add innovation to our games, broadening the portfolio and exploring new territories in mid- core and casual. We take the art and science of gaming to the next level through our curiosity for the unexplored, passion for games, respect for each other and love for our players - and we’re not afraid to have fun along the way. In fact, together with our parent company Activision Blizzard and experts around the world, we believe having fun is good for you. There has never been a better time to join us. We're dreaming bigger and see a world of possibilities ahead. If you share our passion, our values, and our hunger to shape the future, join us in Making the World Playful!
Applications need to be in English.
Discover King at careers.king.com

Title: SCP Technical Lead HPC Applications & Workflows
Description:
SCP Technical Lead HPC Applications & Workflows
Location: Waltham (US), Gothenburg (SWE), Gaithersburg (US), Macclesfield (UK),
ABOUT ASTRAZENECA
AstraZeneca is a global, innovation-driven biopharmaceutical business that focuses on the discovery, development, and commercialisation of prescription medicines for some of the world’s most serious diseases. But we’re more than one of the world’s leading pharmaceutical companies. At AstraZeneca, we’re proud to have a unique workplace culture that inspires innovation and collaboration. Here, employees are empowered to express diverse perspectives and are made to feel valued, energised and rewarded for their ideas and creativity.
ABOUT OUR RESEARCH DATA AND ANALYTICS TEAM
The Research Data & Analytics Team within R&D IT is a global team of highly experienced, skilled data and AI engineers and professionals, passionate about delivering innovative services and products. The mission of our team is to transform the way the R&D discovers and develops medicine through data, analytics, and AI. To achieve this, we partner with scientific teams to deliver groundbreaking capabilities, products and platforms that enable scientists to accelerate medicines that are safe and effective for patients.
SCIENTIFIC COMPUTING PLATFORM
The Scientific Computing platform (SCP) is a foundational capability for HPC and scaled computing solutions. Embedded within the Research D&A organisation it is central to analytics products focused on computational chemistry, imaging, multi-OMICs, structural biology, data science and AI.
We are accountable for the end-to-end delivery of high-performance analytics products, with an emphasis on augmenting the HPC experience. We combine modern HPC with a powerful DevOps stack and cloud-native technologies to power research and development at AstraZeneca.
ABOUT THE PLATFORM
The SCP team provides the high-performance computing (HPC) platform and optimised applications on which scientists build their workflows. We are driven to accelerate scientific discovery, and achieve this through rapid deployment of applications, optimisation of complex workflows and application tuning for very large problems. An overarching principle is to maximise the impact of the team's support efforts.
We are seeking a passionate, HPC applications specialist to join the team as a Technical Lead with responsibility for applications strategy, delivery and support. The ideal candidate will have extensive hands-on experience making an impact with HPC technology, be able to relate to the scientific community and also play a leading role within the platform team.
The HPC applications landscape is continually evolving. You will be responsible for sourcing the optimal technologies to deliver industry-leading capabilities, including application build frameworks, containerised applications and cloud software-as-a-service. Automated application deployment is a key feature and the Technical lead for Applications will have oversight of the end-to-end application process, from creating build templates and testing through version control and automated deployment.
You will work directly with key customers to understand the current and future computational and AI challenges. In response to new project requirements, you will help architect solutions using the platform portfolio of existing services or create new services together with a development team, and maintain ongoing relationships with key users and R&D partners.
Within the leadership team, collaborate to define future platform architectures, software paradigms and support models to face the next generation of computational challenges. Expect to promote the team's work internally and externally through seminars, posters and capability demonstrations.
Key Accountabilities
Defining standards for application deployment, testing and lifecycle management including the use of build frameworks such as Easybuild and CI/CD
Overall responsibility for the application service across our platforms, including how-to guides, efficient job scheduling, and application tuning and benchmarking
Promote optimal use of HPC technologies such as MPI, GPUs and high-speed, low latency storage
Technical leadership for diagnostic activities, such as solving application scalability or data bottleneck issues
Support the overall platform mission, and actively shape strategic direction as a member of the leadership team
Support strong community engagement and communicate news and updates
Candidate Knowledge, Skills, and Experience
Bachelor's, Masters or Doctorate degree in a quantitative or engineering field or equivalent work experience delivering innovative HPC and/or AI/ML solutions
Advanced knowledge of Linux systems and HPC cluster technologies, including a job scheduler such as SLURM
Experience with frameworks for software distribution services such CernVM-File System (CernVM-FS), Easybuild, and Spack
Excellent programming and debugging skills in a scripting language such as Python, Perl or Unix shell
Proficient in compiling software from source code, including debugging errors and resolving dependencies
Hands-on knowledge of a range of scientific and HPC applications such as simulation software, bioinformatics tools or 3D data visualisation packages
Experience in profiling and benchmarking HPC applications in distributed environments for example using tools like Perf, Likwid, NVIDIA Nsight, Intel Vtune Profiler
Familiarity with container runtimes such as Docker, Singularity or enroot
Desirable Skills and Knowledge
Knowledge in a specific domain, such as deep learning, medical imaging, molecular dynamics or 'omics.
Expertise in GPU technologies such as the NVidia HPC SDK and/or GPU-enabled deep learning frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or MXNet
Experience with parallel programming and libraries, ideally MPI, MPI-IO, OpenCL and OpenACC
Experience with frameworks for regression tests and benchmarks for HPC applications, like Reframe HPC
Hands-on experience working in a DevOps team and using agile methodologies
SO, WHAT NEXT?
If reading the above has tickled your senses and you’re ready to join us, hit the apply button and we look forward to reviewing your application soon.

Title: Data Engineer inom Analytics/Business Intelligence
Description:
Slutdatum för platsannonsering/sista ansökningsdatum:
2023-02-28
Om företaget / verksamheten
Drivs du av att utveckla analytics-lösningar och att omvandla data till affärsmöjligheter? Som data engineer i LKAB kommer du att arbeta i en toppmodern dataplattform, som baseras på ETL/ELT-verktyg, data warehouse och system för datahantering.
Avdelningen Digitalisering och Koncern IT består idag av cirka 90 IT-förmågor. Vi söker nu någon som kan förstärka vår grupp Data & Analytics, som har sin huvudfokus på drift, förvaltning och utveckling av lösningar inom beslutsstöd.
Om tjänsten
Som data engineer kommer du att arbeta i LKAB:s dataplattform, som baseras på Wherescape som automations- och ELT-verktyg och Snowflake som datalager. Dataplattformen är en viktig del i LKAB:s data- och analyslandskap och du kommer ha stora möjligheter att påverka och driva utvecklingen av plattformen.
I arbetet kommer du delta i att designa, modellera och utveckla rapporterings- och analyslösningar som hjälper LKAB:s organisation med bättre beslutsstöd, för att bättre se, förstå och agera utifrån sin data.
Du kommer även ingå i vårt analytics-team där du i samarbete med BI-utvecklare, representanter från verksamheter och data scientists säkerställa att data är upptäckbart, tillgängligt och av rätt kvalitet.
Dina arbetsuppgifter består av att samla in data från källor, tillsammans med verksamheten säkerställa att data är av hög kvalitet och designa lösningar som möjliggör analys.
De viktigaste uppgifterna är:
Utifrån verksamhetens behov designa och skapa stjärnscheman i datalagret
Samarbeta med Power BI-utvecklare i teamet för att säkerställa att datamodellerna är optimerade för analys
Skapa förutsättningar för AI, ML och data science
Bidra med idéer kring arbetssätt kopplat till dataplattformen
Att driva ständiga förbättringar inom området är en självklar del i arbetet.
Dina kvalifikationer
Vi söker dig som ha en IT-utbildning på högskolenivå eller motsvarande arbetslivserfarenhet. Du har erfarenhet av SQL, ETL/ELT-utveckling, datamodellering och data warehousing.
Som person bör du ha en god kommunikationsförmåga som du kan anpassa till alla typer av intressenter och du ska ha goda kunskaper i svenska och engelska såväl i tal som skrift. Du behöver vara konsultmässig och ha lätt för att få förtroende från verksamhet, kollegor och leverantörer.
Det är meriterande om du har erfarenhet av:
Wherescape, Informatica eller Snowflake
Bygga data pipelines med hjälp av Python
Versionshantering och CI/CD
Erfarenhet av verktyg och plattformar inom datahantering, som exempelvis Informatica.
B-körkort och gymnasial examen är ett krav för alla tjänster inom LKAB.
Övrig information
För mer information om tjänsten, vänligen kontakta gruppchef Daniel Nordvall, 072-707 67 01 alt.
daniel.nordvall@lkab.com

Vi erbjuder
Vår unika verksamhet kräver anställda med unik kunskap. Oavsett tjänst hjälper och stöttar vi varandra – över avdelnings- och organisationsgränser – inom hela koncernen. Det är viktigt för oss att du vill bidra till den varma och inkluderande kultur som ligger till grund för vår framgång. Vi drivs alla av ett starkt engagemang och vill skapa värde för våra kunder. Vi gillar utmaningar och välkomnar nya idéer. Vi bygger förtroende genom att ta ansvar och hos oss kommer alltid säkerheten först. Våra värderingar är alltså engagemang, innovation och ansvar. Förutom att bli en del av vår breda organisation med gott om möjligheter till utbildning och utveckling i ditt dagliga arbete erbjuder vi alla medarbetare ett attraktivt utbud av förmåner.

Title: Senior AI Platform Engineer
Description:
Senior AI Platform Engineer
Horizon Place; Macclesfield - UK / Gothenburg – Sweden
Competitive salary & benefits
Closing Date: 8th Feb 2023
Do you have expertise in, and passion to work as an AI Platform Engineer by joining the Enterprise AI Platforms and Operations Team? Would you like to apply your expertise in a company that follows the science and turns ideas into life changing medicines? Then AstraZeneca might be the one for you!
About AstraZeneca
AstraZeneca is a global, innovation-driven Biopharmaceutical business that focuses on the discovery, development, and commercialization of prescription medicines for some of the world’s most serious diseases. But we’re more than one of the world’s leading pharmaceutical companies.
There are countless opportunities to develop and grow with AstraZeneca – working with top people to build a diverse career and learn what Commercial looks like at its best. A crucial step on the journey to being a future leader – it’s a fantastic opportunity if you’re up for the challenge.
As a member of the Association of the British Pharmaceutical Industry (ABPI), all of our sales, marketing and communications activities are subject to the ABPI Code of Practice. If you’re encouraged by the possibilities of science to make a difference and ready to discover what you can do – join us!
What you’ll do
As an AI Platform Engineer with an interest in building complex systems, you will be responsible for inventing how we use technology, machine learning, and data to enable the productivity of AstraZeneca. You will help build, deploy and develop our next generation of platforms and tools at scale.
Collaborate with Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers from across the company to understand their challenges and work with them to build the platform that underpins their research
Be a part of a hard-working agile team, continuously improving AstraZeneca’s Machine Learning development environments, platforms, and tooling
Adapt standard machine learning methods to best exploit modern parallel environments (e.g., distributed clusters, multicore SMP, and GPU).
Work closely and collaboratively with internal governance and compliance functions such as Cyber Security and Data Privacy to secure our estate without obstructing end-user productivity.
Champion a “production first mindset” to ensure the necessary infrastructure and platforms are available to scale exploratory research to production.
Liaise with other teams to enhance our technological stack, to enable the adoption of the latest advances in Data Processing and AI.
Provide the vital AWS Services to support the deployment and monitoring of ML solutions in production Optimizing solutions for performance and scalability.
Essential for the role
Significant experience with AWS cloud environments & services (e.g., SageMaker, Athena, S3, EC2, RDS, Glue, etc.) is essential.
Demonstrable knowledge of building data science and machine learning environments to a production standard.
Modern DevOps mindset, using best of breed DevOps toolchains, such as Docker, Git.
Experience with infrastructure as code technology such as Ansible, Terraform and Cloud Formation
Adapt standard machine learning methods to best exploit modern parallel environments (e.g., distributed clusters, multicore SMP, and GPU)
Strong software coding skills, with proficiency in Python, however exceptional ability in any language will be recognized.
Experience with SAFe agile principles and practices.
Experience working with internal security standards and frameworks
Desirable for the role
Experience in implementing & maintaining GxP compliant life science systems, will be looked upon favorably
Certification in appropriate areas will be viewed favorably. Experience building large scale data processing pipelines. e. g. Hadoop/Spark and SQL.
Multi cloud experience (AWS/Azure/GCP)
Why AstraZeneca?
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being an outstanding Place to Work. Where you are empowered to push the boundaries of science and spark your high-reaching spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients, and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and partnership, and always committed to lifelong learning, growth, and development. We’re on an exciting journey to pioneer the future of healthcare.
So, what’s next?
Are you ready to bring new insights and fresh thinking to the table? Brilliant! We have one seat available, and we hope it’s yours.

Title: Experienced CRA
Description:
Job Overview
Perform monitoring and site management work to ensure that sites are conducting the study(ies) and reporting study data as required by the study protocol, applicable regulations and guidelines, and sponsor requirements.
Essential Functions
Perform site monitoring visits (selection, initiation, monitoring and close-out visits) in accordance with contracted scope of work and regulatory requirements, i.e., Good Clinical Practice (GCP) and International Conference on Harmonization (ICH) guidelines.
Work with sites to adapt, drive and track subject recruitment plan in line with project needs to enhance predictability.
Administer protocol and related study training to assigned sites and establish regular lines of communication with sites to manage ongoing project expectations and issues.
Evaluate the quality and integrity of study site practices related to the proper conduct of the protocol and adherence to applicable regulations. Escalate quality issues as appropriate.
Manage the progress of assigned studies by tracking regulatory submissions and approvals, recruitment and enrollment, case report form (CRF) completion and submission, and data query generation and resolution. May support start-up phase.
Ensure copies/originals (as required) site documents are available for filing in the Trial Master File (TMF) verify that the Investigator's Site File (ISF) is maintained in accordance with GCP / ICH and local regulatory requirements.
Create and maintain appropriate documentation regarding site management, monitoring visit findings and action plans by submitting regular visit reports, generating follow-up letters and other required study documentation.
Collaborate and liaise with study team members for project execution support as appropriate.
If applicable, may be accountable for supporting development of project subject recruitment plan on a per site basis.
If applicable, may be accountable for site financial management according to executed clinical trial agreement and retrieve invoices according to local requirement.
Qualifications
High School Diploma or equivalent Degree in scientific discipline or health care preferred.
Equivalent combination of education, training and experience may be accepted in lieu of degree.
Some organizations require completion of CRA training program or prior monitoring experience.
Basic knowledge of, and skill in applying, applicable clinical research regulatory requirements (i.e., Good Clinical Practice (GCP) and International Conference on Harmonization (ICH) guidelines).
Good therapeutic and protocol knowledge as provided in company training.
Computer skills including proficiency in use of Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint and use of a laptop computer and iPhone and iPad (where applicable).
Written and verbal communication skills including good command of English language.
Organizational and problem-solving skills.
Effective time and financial management skills.
Ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with coworkers, managers, and clients.
IQVIA is a leading global provider of advanced analytics, technology solutions and clinical research services to the life sciences industry. We believe in pushing the boundaries of human science and data science to make the biggest impact possible – to help our customers create a healthier world. Learn more at https://jobs.iqvia.com

Title: Data Engineer (f/m/d)
Description:
Data Engineer
About the Role
We strongly believe that in this digital age for a sustainable competitiveness it is imperative to have a strong focus on Data & Analytics cutting across Business Services. We are heavily investing in areas like Big Data, Data Science, Reporting, and BI Tools to meet our Digital transformation objectives. We are looking for an experienced professional in the role of Data Engineer to help us in achieving the same. In this role of Data Engineer, you will work across various Data & Analytics Tools, Applications, and Big Data Platforms.
You feel ownership (and are responsible) for the data, as key company asset and driving, govern, and guide teams and know how to maximise value and balance speed and quality in delivery. You are aware about the best practices in Data & Analytics domain and you know the best way to utilise them or you are keen to learn and share your findings with others. As part of the Analytics Microsoft Delivery team you will be working closely with Data Science, Enterprise Architecture, and Business Unit teams to contribute towards the data strategy; as well as with Application Architects and Solution Architects to implement coherent solution architecture and learn from each other.
We’re looking for people who embody our values, aren’t afraid to challenge, innovate, experiment, and move at a fast pace. We’re always looking for ways to improve our products and ourselves. If this is you, we’d love to talk.

Contribute to delivering business impact and finding and implementing effective solutions in a matrix organisation to drive the enterprise information strategy and analytics transformation
Take a leading role in operationalising data science models to ensure all requirements, including functional, integration, security, performance, quality, and operations are covered

Ensure that developed solutions are peer reviewed and formally documented according to company IT standards

Significant experince of application programming (python or Scala) and ETL/ELT experience
Experience with big data technologies including Hadoop, Apache Spark • More than two years working experience with Databricks and Microsoft Azure Data Lake tools (Azure Data Lake, Azure Databricks, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Warehouse, Power BI, Logic Apps)
More than one year working experience building automation pipelines for testing and deployment using Azure DevOps
Experience working with creating restful APIs and creating external applications to run data science models

Advanced knowledge of Python to be able to perform code refactoring

Basic understanding of data science

Collaborative and Inclusive Culture | Empowering & Engaged Leaders | Working with Powerful Purpose & Sustainable Impact | Learning and Growing in your Career | Supporting Well-being & Sustainable Working Life | Life-changing Innovations | Competitive Total rewards

Working at Essity is not just a career; it is a chance to directly make the world a healthier, more hygienic and safer place. With impactful innovations coupled with sustainable solutions, we strive to reach more people every year with the necessary and essential solutions for well-being.

Title: Head of Analytics
Description:
Do you want to help us unleash the secret to how happy employees create a happy business? We are an innovative, agile, and continuously growing modern tech company on a path to improving the work lives of millions around the world.

We develop workforce management solutions - software that makes scheduling and time reporting more smooth and more flexible for almost a million users worldwide!

We value passion, creativity, quality, and simplicity. You’ll be given the opportunity to make an impact and directly contribute to our success, bring new ideas, and have full ownership of your area.

Our global team, of more than 35 nationalities, have fun together, whether it is during a typical Swedish Fika, a workshop, going for a run with a colleague, or spending time together during the annual company Goal trip, team kickoffs, or after-work socials. The mission is to turn our vast amounts of data into actionable insights across the organisation and guide the development of new features and models. The Head of Analytics will lead our analytics team, and work closely with stakeholders and cross-functional teams to leverage data-driven insights to drive business growth. With our international presence, you will be an integral part of a company set out to enable our customers to create a happy business and a happy workforce.

Are you a data and analytics leader with a passion for driving analytics initiatives? Do you have a strong background in data engineering, data analysis, and data science, as well as technical proficiency in programming languages and tools? What you’ll be doing

Lead a team within data analysis, data engineering, and data science to deliver high-quality insights, analysis, and models that inform key business decisions
Develop and drive the vision, strategy, and execution of the analytics function within the organisation
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to identify opportunities for data-driven innovation and optimization
Ensure the right technical capabilities, tools, and systems are in place to support the analytics efforts
Build and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders to ensure alignment on analytics priorities and objectives
Mentor and develop team members to ensure they have the skills and knowledge needed to grow and deliver high-quality work
Stay ahead of industry trends and best practices
What you’ll bring to the team

MSc degree in Engineering, Physics, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, or equivalent quantitative field.
4+ years of experience managing data & analytics teams
Strong leadership skills and a track record of leading by example
Strong skill set and profound background in the data & analytics field spanning from data engineering, analysis to science.
Technical proficiency in programming languages and tools such as Python, Spark, SQL, R, and data visualisation tools.
Strategic mindset with great business acumen
Ability to build and maintain strong relationships with stakeholders at all levels of the organisation
Strong communication skills
Experience working within the SaaS space
What’s in it for you?

We promote and encourage a healthy lifestyle with flexible work hours and the latest tools, enhanced vacation allowance, wellness, home office, professional development contributions, virtual yoga classes, and last but not least, you will have the chance to participate in our well-known yearly ping-pong tournament!
