If you want.

It’s up to you. We give you the opportunities, and you decide what suits you and your life.

Title: Machine Learning Engineer
Description:
The Babyshop Group is a global premium and luxury retailer of children's clothing and products to the modern family. The Group operates babyshop.com, lekmer.se, melijoe.com and alexandalexa.com as well as a number of retail stores. Babyshop offers more than 500 prestige brands along with a number of proprietary brands like e.g. Kuling, STOY and a Happy Brand. With an annual sales run rate of over €100 million, catering +100 countries and reaching over 1,000,000 customers Babyshop Group is a leading player with a global footprint.

For further information see www.babyshop.com

ABOUT THE POSITION

Data plays a vital role in Babyshop’s organisation, enabling data-driven decisions supported by both ad-hoc analysis as well as highly complex ML-models. We have machine learning models deployed, leveraging massive amounts of data, within multiple areas such as recommender systems, search & rank, demand predictions, CLV-predictions and attribution models to name some. You will join the Data Team where you will develop production grade code, ML-algorithms as well as infrastructure to ensure reliability and scalability. The Data Team consists of a core team with different expertise; Data Engineer, Data Analyst, Data Scientist, BI Developer, ML Engineer etc, working with data in all stages. We believe that how we leverage data, accompanied by a customer-centric mindset, is the differentiating factor and are looking for an individual who shares that belief.

WHAT YOU'LL DO

Produce high quality code, leveraging software development as well as ML-Ops best practices, to create long-lasting, easily maintainable, code and algorithms.
Design, engineer and improve algorithms focused on a broad set of use-cases; recommender systems, ranking, CLV-predictions, Attribution modelling, Purchase probability predictions etc.
Being an integral part in the full lifecycle of ML-development: Forming hypotheses, data munging raw data, setting up experiments as well as evaluating them. This, followed by full-scale deployment into production, with continuous re-training, validation and monitoring.
Help idealise, plan and deliver intelligent algorithms, at scale, while working closely with business and tech to meet ambitious goals..
Integrate ML-algorithms into the platform, both independently and in close collaboration with software developers.
Contribute to innovation within the company, coming up with new ways to leverage ML and data.
WHO YOU ARE

You have a MSc in Statistics, Mathematics, Machine Learning, Computer Science/Information Technology, Economics/Econometrics or other quantitative scientific discipline and/or relevant work experience.
You believe good code is as important as good algorithms.
You are fluent in SQL (we use Snowflake), Python (which is our core language) and Data Science & ML packages (Pandas, scikit-learn, TensorFlow etc).
You have experience engineering and implementing tree based models and deep learning architectures.
You have a good understanding of cloud technologies (we use GCP).
You are pragmatic in how you approach problems, understanding it starts with fully grasping the problem and ends with engineering the solution, not the other way around.
You are not afraid of trying out new tools or technologies, and have an aspiration to continuously develop.
You are interested in keeping up to date with scientific advancements, both in the modelling field as well as the ML-Ops field.
You are a strong English communicator, both written and spoken.
IT’S A PLUS IF YOU ...

Have experience deploying ML-models into production, as well as the surrounding infrastructure including Docker, Kubernetes and ML-pipeline orchestration tools (we use Kubeflow Pipelines & Vertex AI).
THE TEAM AND WORKPLACE

The Babyshop Group headquarter is in Stockholm with additional offices in Oslo and Paris. You find our modern automated warehouse and data-driven Customer Service and Photo studio in Jönköping. The position is based in our HQ office in Stockholm, Östermalm. As a Machine Learning Engineer you report to the Head of Data and belong to the Babyshop Group Tech-organization.

Sounds interesting? Click on the “Apply” below to submit your application, where we encourage you to attach both CV and Cover Letter! The last day to submit is 2023-02-28 however applications will be reviewed continuously. Good luck!

Start: As soon as possible
Extent: 40h/week, Permanent employment with six months’ probation period. Flexible working hours apply.
Where? HQ in Stockholm, Östermalm.

Title: Senior Data Analyst - 13955

Do you have data science experience, and are seeking a new job in Stockholm? Skillsearch is helping a gaming company find a full-time Data Scientist, and the role comes with an attractive salary and benefits package.

Experience making ETLs and data pipelines
As a vital member of our team and in return for your expertise, inclusive approach and commitment, we will provide a favourable salary and the chance to join a passionate and welcoming team.

Title: R&D Scientist in Automated Trading and Energy Market Analytics
Description:
At Hitachi Energy our purpose is advancing a sustainable energy future for all. We bring power to our homes, schools, hospitals and factories. Join us and work with fantastic people, while learning and developing yourself on projects that have a real impact to our communities and society. Bring your passion, bring your energy, and be part of a global team that appreciates a simple truth: Diversity + Collaboration = Great Innovation
Hitachi Energy Research are looking for a Researcher with expertise in the area of Automated Trading and Energy Market Analytics. You will join a dynamic, motivated and creative team with a broad range of experience and competences. As part of our team you will combine theory with practice, creating, testing and validating new technologies to enable the energy transition. For this position you can be located at one of our research centers in Mannheim/Germany, Baden/Switzerland, Montreal/Canada, Raleigh/US, Krakow/Poland or Västeras/Sweden.
Your responsibilities
Propose, contribute to and lead research projects designing trading solutions for energy markets (electricity, non-electric energy, multi-energy systems, CO2 compensation), risk management, strategic investment and intelligence tools.
Be the energy trading domain expert in our interdisciplinary team, collaborating with experts in power systems, AI, optimization, mathematics, data science, SW and human-computer interaction.
Propose investigate, and develop automated trading solutions with business impact, turn them into prototypes and verify them.
Develop concepts for combining models of energy markets with new and emerging technologies such as Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence.
Network in the company and actively distribute your knowledge and expertise.
Collaborate with local and global external partners including universities, open-source communities, startups and vendors.
Disseminate your results in scientific publications, patent applications, and technical reports.
Your background
Strong academic qualification with an internationally recognized degree at masters or doctorate level in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Power Systems Engineering, or any related field.
In-depth knowledge of energy planning and trading solutions, including aspects such as market analytics, market data automation and integration solutions and trading and risk management.
Software development experience to develop trading algorithms.
Experience that demonstrates your team-oriented, innovative, and strategic working styles.
Fluency in English, both written and spoken.
More about us
Hitachi Energy is a global technology leader that is advancing a sustainable energy future for all. We serve customers in the utility, industry and infrastructure sectors with innovative solutions and services across the value chain. Together with customers and partners, we pioneer technologies and enable the digital transformation required to accelerate the energy transition towards a carbon-neutral future. We are advancing the world’s energy system to become more sustainable, flexible and secure whilst balancing social, environmental and economic value. Hitachi Energy has a proven track record and unparalleled installed base in more than 140 countries. Headquartered in Switzerland, we employ around 38,000 people in 90 countries and generate business volumes of approximately $10 billion USD. www.hitachienergy.com

Title: Sustainability and EHS Business Analyst
Description:
Come join our professional team – delivering top class service and specialist knowledge! To Sandvik Machining Solutions(SMS), hosted in the Division Seco Tools and this new role, we’re now looking for a Sustainability and EHS Business Analyst. Take the chance to be part of our exciting world!
A genuine interest in our customers’ success, our family spirit and personal commitment are the values that summarize our corporate culture. These values reflect a shared view of the business and unite Seco’s employees across both geographical and cultural borders. EHS and sustainability are our main priorities, and we actively and consciously work to create a culture where safety always comes first – regardless of the circumstances.
About the job
In this position, you provide proactive decision support and recommendations by developing and analyzing EHS and Sustainability data and performance indicators. You also perform the required reporting of EHS and Sustainability data according to internal and external requirements. In this role, you work closely to the chair of SMS Sustainability & EHS Council.

Also included in your job:
Design efficient and relevant reporting structures and tools for Sustainability and EHS at SMS.
Responsible to consolidate data from various sources and create required analysis and reports.
Collaborate with stakeholders and be proactive in building subject expertise and awareness of future demands on company sustainability reporting. Coordinate work within SMS to gather needed data for required Sustainability and EHS reporting.
Proactively perform data analysis to inform about development and support decision making, as well as external trend reporting.
Administration and arrangement connected to SMS Sustainability & EHS Council.

The location for this position is in Fagersta, Sweden, or flexible within central Europe. However, we also offer part-time remote work possibilities, and some travel is included in your job.
Your profile
We’re looking for someone with a university degree in business administration or data science. You have a background from working in a similar role in industrial manufacturing in a global setting – for example process development, management, development of procedures or definitions.

We also appreciate your:
Experience from working with process development/management, developing procedures and definitions.
Knowledge in various sustainability requirements.
Awareness of auditing and internal control procedures.
Knowledge in software solutions and a sense for technical opportunities.
Microsoft 360 solutions experience, especially for Power BI and Excel.
Subject matter expertise and awareness of future demands on company sustainability reporting.
Awareness of Sustainability Reporting Frameworks and internationally accepted frameworks for disclosing climate related information.
Excellent English skills, both in written and verbal.

Your personality contributes to our success! This position requires analytical and problem-solving skills, and your thorough approach allows you to both keep an overall view while paying close attention details. You’re result-oriented and have the ability to identify solutions – taking great pride in delivering high quality in a timely manner.
Our Seco culture
Seco employees across the globe share our family spirit, along with a passion for our customers and a personal commitment to ensure success in everything we do. For us, it’s also clear that our diversities form an amazing foundation for achieving great results. Visit our LinkedIn or Facebook to get to know us and our products further.
Application
Send your application no later than February 20, 2023. Read more about us and apply at secotools.com (Job ID: R0050324).

At Seco Tools we develop and offer advanced products & solutions that make metal cutting easier. We work together with our customers to identify and implement the best solutions for their needs. The corporate culture empowers employees through shared values: Passion for our customers, Family Spirit, Personal commitment. Title: Data Engineer to Vetfamily
Description:
Do you have a passion for well-structured data pipelines and want to be responsible for developing and maintaining our data warehouse?

Vimian is a global and diversified group of innovation-driven companies with a shared passion for making a positive impact through improving animal health. Together we put science, technology and our customer’s needs at the centre of everything we do to deliver effective solutions to veterinary professionals, labs and pet owners around the world.

We are looking for a self-driven, structured Data Warehouse Engineer to join our IT & BI team and lead the work in extending the Financial Data Warehouse into an insight generating business platform. We are looking for candidates with understanding of ERP systems and Financial Book Keeping and having a track record of operating system with a multitude of sources. The right candidate will find an exciting role leading a highly prioritized project within the financially stable and fast growing international Vimian Group.

What you will do:
Take over ownership of the established, well architectured and documented data warehouse platform which runs on Azure with Data factory, Synapse and powerBI.
Ensure the integrity of the dataware house architecture as you extend it with additional sources of data.
Continuously extend the pipelines as new companies are acquired and onboarded.
Jointly with the rest of the powerBI team, collaborate with Group Management, Finance, and operations to provide data analysis to answer business questions.
Ensure the DWH transforms the data into usable and presentable insight.
Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure the established data definitions match their expectations.
With us, you will be leading highly prioritized projects to spread data accessibility and usage through data pipelines across the Vimian Group.
Ensure a stable and reliable DWH that can deliver key financial data even during critical reporting periods.
Is this you?

Structured and self motivated.
Ability to maintain architecture while growing features and extending pipelines.
Bachelor or Master’s degree in Computer Science or Data science.
4+ years data engineering experience as a BI developer or software engineer.
Experience with Azure Synapse, Azure Devops, Azure Data factory powerBI. Or extensive experience with similar tools and a willingness and ability to quickly learn new tools.
Expert knowledge of SQL, Cloud Hosted Data warehouse Management.
Scripting knowledge.

Title: Senior Solution Architect
Description:
Senior Solution Architect
Do you have expertise in, and passion for, Architecture? Would you like to apply your expertise to impact a company that follows the science and turns ideas into life changing medicines? If so, AstraZeneca might be the one for you!
ABOUT ASTRAZENECA
AstraZeneca is a global, innovation-driven BioPharmaceutical business that focuses on the discovery, development and commercialisation of prescription medicines for some of the world’s most serious disease. But we’re more than one of the world’s leading pharmaceutical companies.
At AstraZeneca we’re dedicated to being a Great Place to Work. Where you are empowered to push the boundaries of science and unleash your entrepreneurial spirit. There’s no better place to make a difference to medicine, patients and society. An inclusive culture that champions diversity and collaboration. Always committed to lifelong learning, growth and development.
ABOUT THE ROLE?
The Senior Solution Architect is accountable for determining and architecting solutions that enable the desired business capabilities, delivering in alignment with AstraZeneca’s IT strategy, roadmap, principles and standards. They work with other Solution Architects in the Manufacturing domain and experience in this domain is essential.
The Senior Solution Architect ensures that AZ technical solutions are delivered to AZ defined reference architecture and technology standards, and this includes the definition of such standards where there are capability gaps. The role will ensure that common architecture decisions are implemented consistently across the business and IT.
The role will provide Information Technology architectural expertise and technical direction to system development and integration projects. The Architect will work on architectures for business solutions and will specialise in at least one architecture domain, with the aligned domain for this role being the Manufacturing domain within the Operations group.
ABOUT OUR IT ARCHITECTURE TEAM

As Architects, we connect the dots across the business to improve the agility and functionality of our processes to accelerate AstraZeneca to the next level. There’s so much potential to influence and inspire change, it’s a big challenge if you’re up for it. As champions of our Technology ecosystem, we make sure the rest of the business experiences the true benefits of our systems. Uniting diverse areas and simplifying the way we work, changing approaches and behaviours along the way – our reach goes beyond technology. It starts with a holistic view, connecting emerging trends with business ambitions and applying emotional intelligence to understand how we can guide the right way to work and behave. Across the enterprise and each technology domain we come together to find leading solutions that will provide the platform for AstraZeneca’s success. Change agents, we are always proactively hunting for new insights and problem-solving to identify better ways of doing things. Motivated by the opportunities to learn and grow, we move fast and drive forward. Lay the foundations for future technological and people-driven success across AstraZeneca.
Candidate Focus & Challenge
Senior Solution Architect for IGNITE: Operations IT (MAKE) Architecture
This role is accountable for the solution architecture and design across AstraZeneca’s Operations domains eg Manufacturing & Supply Chain with a focus on Data & Analytics capabilities.
You will be the responsible architect on projects within areas including but not limited to: Smart Factory, Digital Uplift, Digital Transformation and Lifecycle Refresh Programmes. You will be required to analyse, conceptualise, design and govern across AstraZeneca’s strategic IT landscape to in order to support business projects.
Accountable for architecting and designing comprehensive solutions that meet business requirements and are aligned to AstraZeneca’s Enterprise Architecture, in support of a given portfolio
Design architectures and delivers documentation for projects or solutions in order to address business/application/data/infrastructure requirements
Ensure that solution architectures and designs are appropriately robust and address business, application, information and infrastructure architectural requirements
Ensure analysis and design is documented in supporting Architectural Artefacts ie Solution Blueprint and seeks Architecture Review Board Signoff.
Work with Business Analysis and Solution Engineering functions to support functional & technical requirements management, including providing senior architecture support in key processes including technology acquisition
Partner with project managers, business analysts, and solution engineers to create solutions that are aligned to AstraZeneca architecture standards and principles, leverage common solutions and services, and meet the financial targets (cost and benefits)
Support the Enterprise Architect in defining technology roadmaps.
Within the solution development lifecycle, the role will be accountable for solution evaluation and selection, buy vs. build decisions, and early-phase project estimates which contribute to a given case
Provide technical & IT expertise support to project teams and conducts AZ architectural reviews throughout project lifecycle
Ensure compliance with existing EA guidelines and standards (e.g. AZ Architecture Engagement Process (ISPMM) and EA Software Standards)
Contribute to project and service teams in the development, implementation and maintenance of standard architectural components
Work with third party suppliers as required and contributes to the creation of functional design documents
Work with third party suppliers to verify technical development and delivery are in alignment with the Architecture Roadmap
Contribute to the development of the Architecture Capability by documenting and sharing knowledge and standard methodologies with peer Architects
ESSENTIAL SKILLS & EXPERIENCE REQUIRED?
Proven experience of application solution architecture and design experience, with proven capability in data & analytics, AI/ML application architecture and exposure to working in an operations domain, i.e.; manufacturing, supply chain etc.
Relevant technical degree or equivalent
Proven skills and experience being the solution architect on projects and programmes
Experience of Operations domains and processes
Technologies: Relational, Column Store Databases, Big Data technologies, data streaming, real-time inference, Front end tooling PowerBI, QlikSense, Data Science Tooling - SageMaker and other similar platforms, manufacturing system technologies including MES, Historian, OPC
Proven development/design experience in at least one technical domain
Experience of developing innovative solutions, blueprints and standards for solution design
Experience implementing and maintaining business solution architectures under any formal framework for their domain of architecture
Experience of developing and managing relationships with 3rd party suppliers
Excellent analytical skills
Excellent communication, facilitation and relationship management skills
Strong networking skills with good internal/external links
Ability to interpret and communicate technical information into business language
Evidence of shaping innovative solutions that have a major impact within the business area and organisation
Excellent business acumen and strong knowledge of procurement business processes
Demonstrated initiative, strong customer orientation, and cross-cultural working
Experience working in a global organization where partners and project team members are geographically dispersed
Ability to travel to AstraZeneca’s global Operations sites
Ability to work well in diverse, multinational teams and proven ability to influence others to achieve positive outcomes
WHY JOIN IT?
We’re a network of entrepreneurial self-starters who contribute to something far bigger. There’s a diversity of expertise in our Technology group that’s unique to AstraZeneca – it allows us to dive deep into exploring new groundbreaking technology. We enable AstraZeneca to perform at its peak by delivering world-class technology and data solutions. Our work unlocks the potential of science. We optimise and evolutionise AstraZeneca by maximising efficiencies and finding new ways to drive productivity. From automation to data simplification. We’re not afraid to take ownership and run with it. Empowered with unrivalled freedom. A place to be open and transparent – we speak up, think creatively and share ideas. Our diverse contributions help us to make better decisions. But we have a constant drive to innovate, and an appreciation for high standards. It takes challenging the status quo to contribute in our ever-evolving environment. We love it here because put simply, we make a meaningful impact.
Technology at AstraZeneca is a home for purposeful disruptors!
SO, WHAT’S NEXT?
Are you already imagining yourself joining our team? Good, because we’d love to hear from you! Click the link to apply and we’ll be in touch as soon as we can.
WHERE CAN I FIND OUT MORE?
Our Social Media, Follow AstraZeneca on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/1603/
Follow AstraZeneca on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/astrazenecacareers/
Follow AstraZeneca on Instagram https://www.instagram.com/astrazeneca_careers/?hl=en
Competitive salary & benefits on offer.
Close Date: 5/2/2023

Title: Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD
Description:
Join us on our journey to net zero. We are looking for a Machine Learning Engineer OBM/OBD to join our R&D team.

At Aurobay, we are re-imagining motion for a brighter tomorrow. That means challenging accepted beliefs and pushing the boundaries of what you’ve done before. But you won’t have to do it alone. You’ll be working alongside fantastic people who are caring and collaborative, with a global mindset, and a commitment to creating excellence.

Do you fit the profile?
As a Machine Learning Engineer, you’ll be helping to shape the future of sustainable powertrain development. Our team currently consists of six data scientists, SW engineers, and model-based calibration engineers. We develop new methods for measurement data collection and analysis to help R&D become more efficient and data driven. We also work closely with other advanced engineering teams.

You will use the data we are collecting in our rigs to build models for predicting engine emissions of hazardous species. The models can be used both offline in the development phase, and on the edge for On-Board Monitoring (OBM) and On-Board Diagnostics (OBD) in our customer vehicles. As part of this job, you’ll have the opportunity develop your own machine-learning projects together with the rest of the team. We give our engineers the freedom and time for their own projects, to try out new ideas and fine-tune their skills.

You will also:
Train and evaluate ML models for predicting emissions
Work closely together with subject matter experts to align data/measurement requirements and incorporate physical models into the model
Optimize algorithm memory and CPU load for predictions on the edge together with function developers
What we offer

Although we are proud of our heritage at Volvo Cars and Geely, this is a start-up environment, where you’ll be helping to create the Aurobay of tomorrow. You’ll get plenty of both formal and informal opportunities for learning and development. Joining Aurobay will give you a platform for personal and professional development, and a springboard for your future career.

What you’ll get

We’re passionate about sharing our success and making sure you’re well rewarded, from pay and bonuses to the company pension. Our benefits are designed to improve your life at work and at home, with health and wellbeing support, life and travel insurance, and a timebank you can use to flex your work-life balance:

Competitive salary
Wellness contribution of up to SEK 5 000/year
A personal and professional development scheme to support your growth.
Want to drive a car? - Discount to buy a car, and a competitive leasing cost for a company car.
Additional pension funding.
Competitive additional and full-cover insurance.
Other benefits through an industry-leading portal: health and wellness, bicycle, electronics, shopping, to name a few.
What you’ll need

A master’s degree or higher in data science, mathematics, statistics, physics or relevant fields.
Strong programming skills in Python, Julia, or MATLAB.
Experience in ML algorithms such as linear regression, artificial neural networks, and boosted decision tree regression.
Nice to have experience in

Time series modeling, especially ML algorithms that can be used for time series such as recurrent neural networks, convolutional neural networks, or transformers
Internal Combustion Engines
Chemical models for catalytic converters
Embedded systems
We encourage diversity and believe that the different backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives our people bring make us stronger as a company.

Questions

If you have any additional questions regarding the position, you are welcome to contact recruiting manager Erik Fyrk, erik.fyrk@aurobay.com

For questions regarding the recruitment process please contact Recruiter Felicia Eriksson, felicia.eriksson@aurobay.com

Akademikerna: Ordf. Henrik Simonsen, henrik.simonsen@aurobay.com, tel +46708219331

How to apply

Deadline to submit your application is 31st of January, but the selection process will be running continuously. Please note that due to GDPR, we do not accept applications via email.
Good luck with your application!

Title: Senior Backend Engineer
Description:
Joint Academy is a global leader in delivering digital treatment for chronic joint pain, connecting patients with licensed physical therapists. Backed by science, our clinically validated treatment programs include individualized exercises, interactive education and tracking tools. The intersection of digital treatment and data science opens up new possibilities of treating patients in a sustainable and more personal way, while reducing pain and improving quality of life.
With Joint Academy, you’re joining a startup with a global reach beyond its origins in Sweden, treating patients in multiple markets across two continents.
Engineering

Our engineering department consists of ~20 developers creating our platform and applications for patients, physiotherapists and others involved in digital treatment. We are organized in small cross-functional product teams that each focus on specific parts of our products and markets. Our tech stack is currently based on Ruby on Rails, PostgreSQL, Redis, Kubernetes and AWS for the backend, with React and React Native used for our frontend client applications. However, we are building a new backend in Go. This migration will be the primary goal for Engineering the coming year. We are now looking to strengthen our organization and teams with a senior backend engineer that can help us transition away from Ruby to Go as our primary backend language.

What You'll Do
Join a cross functional team of dedicated and skilled software professionals building a cutting-edge e-health platform
Work closely with the product manager, designer and other developers in your team to plan and design the implementation of new features
Design and implement systems and APIs that deliver digital treatment to tens of thousands of patients
Write efficient code to support complex business requirements, meeting the demands of various markets, payment structures, and regulations
Test your code using a range of tools and strategies, both automated and manual
Collaborate with other backend engineers to continuously improve and maintain our platform in a sustainable and scalable way
Requirements
We are looking for developers with experience and passion for building backend services for mobile and web applications.
Apart from writing new features in the new BE architecture using Go, you will also port over existing features from the Ruby on Rails monolith. We are using PostgreSQL as our primary database and it's a plus if you have experience working with PostgreSQL.
Some key points:
You have 5+ years of professional software development experience with a focus on backend systems, APIs and relational databases
You have strong communication skills and understand how to collaborate effectively in a remote environment
You enjoy being part of understanding, planning and scoping the work to achieve set goals, rather than being handed a list of requirements to implement
You take pride in your work and believe that high quality code supported by a solid suite of tests and specifications pay off both in the long and short term
You thrive on the exchange of ideas and criticism, and can both take and give feedback in a friendly atmosphere without prestige getting in the way
Experience with Ruby/Ruby on Rails is a plus but not required if you have worked with similar technologies
You have strong experience working with Go in a professional setting
It is a plus if you have experience working with Kubernetes and AWS
You are based anywhere in Sweden and hold a permanent Swedish job permit
Benefits
You will work with something truly meaningful and a product that has a positive impact on many people's lives globally
You will have the opportunity to work with a unique mix of people with different expertise, including leading academic scientists, medical professionals and experienced product developers
30 days paid vacation
Pension and insurance package
Flexible working hours
Wellness contribution and workout during working hours
Birthdays off
Yearly Volunteering Day to spend on a non profit organisation
Work from a modern office or fully remote, or a hybrid of the two. Our main office is in central Malmö, but some engineers work remotely from anywhere in Sweden.

Title: Cloud Architect
Description:
Cloud Architect
#LI-HYBRID #LI-ML1
The role
Kindred's vision is to be fully data-driven and use data in new ways to drive revenues and provide a better and unique experience for our customers.
To base this vision, we are hiring a cloud architect that can help us leverage cloud technologies to build a best-in-class data platform on AWS (Amazon Web Services).
You will join our architecture team and jointly you will collaborate on taking our data platform to the next level and build analytic and business insight capabilities to empower associates with the right information at the right time for their data-driven decisions.

What you will do
Leverage your knowledge of AWS tools and products to design highly scalable, flexible, and resilient cloud architectures that address our business needs.
Collaborate with other architects on how to solve complex and high-scale data challenges.
Design data processing pipelines and workflows to support data democratisation and enable data-driven decision-making.
Ensure that data pipelines and data stores are high-performing, reliable and well organized.
Collaborate with data science teams on how to use modern data analytic technologies.
Engage in proof-of-concept projects proving the use of AWS services to support new data processing solutions.
Help engineering teams successfully implement applications using AWS cloud services.
Identify options for how to best design our data solutions with performance, data quality, cost control, ease of maintenance and business value for our stakeholders in mind.
Proactively and continuously review our architecture and identify opportunities for the use of innovative technology to deliver more effective solutions.
Work closely with other architects to make sure processes and long-term architectural goals are aligned.

Your experience
You have a strong data engineering & architectural background in designing data-intensive applications at the enterprise level, always with cost control and business value in mind.
You fully understand key concepts in the data ecosystem and can describe and assess the pros and cons of different design options and how to drive value with data.
You know how to get the most value out of things like data pipelines, data lakes, purpose-built data stores, real-time data streams, machine learning, data warehouses, business intelligence and their role in the data ecosystem.
You fully understand key concepts around information security, architectural frameworks and DevOps methodologies.
You have experience with managing data at the enterprise level, where data quality and governance are essential.
Expertise in integrating, transforming and consolidating data from various structured and unstructured data systems into structures that are suitable for building analytics solutions.
Experience with AWS services such as Athena, Glue, Lambda, S3, DynamoDB NoSQL, Relational Database Service (RDS), Amazon EMR and Amazon Redshift.
Experience with Apache Kafka for high-performance data pipelines, streaming analytics, and data integration.
Experience in implementing cost-control strategies in AWS.

Who we think you might be
You are an AWS cloud professional certified architect.
You are analytical and can think strategically about both business and technical challenges.
You stay up to date with the latest trends, tools & technologies, and best practices in the cloud and data space.
You enjoy running workshops using the whiteboard for discussing options and design.
You are a great communicator and can talk about technology with less experienced people.
You enjoy taking initiative and are self-motivated to do an excellent job

Application Process
Click on the "Apply Now" button and complete the short web form. Please add your CV in English to let us know your motivation for applying and your salary expectation. for further queries please reach out to the talent acquisition partner at (Prachi.arya@kindredgroup.com)
Kindred is an equal opportunities employer committed to employing a diverse workforce and an inclusive culture. As such, we oppose all forms of discrimination in the workplace. We create equal opportunities for all our applicants and will treat people equally regardless of and not limited to, gender, age, disability, race, or sexual orientation. We are committed not only to our legal obligations but also to the positive promotion that equal opportunities bring to our operations as set out in our sustainability framework.

Job Alerts
Not suited to this role but interested in working at Kindred Group?
We are always on the lookout for talented, passionate people to join our global teams so if you'd like us to let you know when suitable jobs come up, please click on “Register for Alerts”.

Title: Vill du jobba med testautomation, CI och mjukvaruflöden? Se hit!
Description:
Infotiv är en ingenjörsbyrå med 25 år i branschen och med moderna ambitioner för framtiden. Infotivs affärsområde TechDev ligger i framkant när det kommer till tekniker inom bl a mjukvaruutveckling, testsystem och arbetsmetodik. Detta i kombination med vårt varma hjärta och skarpa hjärna är bestående framgångsfaktorer för oss. Vi nöjer oss inte med att uppfylla förväntningarna, utan vill överträffa dem varje gång.

Just nu letar vi efter dig som inser styrkan i att låta verktygen jobba för dig, och inte du för dem. Du förstår värdet av att automatisera de de lågt hängande frukterna och vet när det är läge att behålla befintliga arbetssätt, för att på så sätt maximera värdet till din omgivning och samtidigt optimera din egen vardag. Vi tror att du känner starka positiva känslor för både testautomation och CI.

Din framtida utmaning

Du kommer att bli del av ett team som jobbar med testning av de viktigaste funktionerna i elsystem för eldrivna fordon. Uppdraget är att utveckla automatiserade testfall som sedan integreras i CI-kedjan. Techstacken består av Robot Framework, C/C#, Python och Vector CANoe, där Jenkins är ryggraden i testexekveringen. Rollen innefattar även interaktion med den fysiska produkten, bl a i form av mjukvaruuppdateringar och felsökning.

Den du är idag

Som person är du engagerad och strävar efter att leverera ditt bästa resultat varje gång. Du andas kod och lever efter devisen “allting går att automatisera”. Självklart är du även intresserad av hårdvaran som realiserar dina visioner. Du är kreativ och nyfiken inför kundens/projektets behov och kan snabbt anpassa dig till olika situationer. Du är social och gillar att arbeta i team och ser spännande utmaningar i de möjligheter som erbjuds.

Kompetenskrav

Goda programmeringskunskaper inom Python, C eller C#
Mycket goda kunskaper inom automationsservrar som Jenkins eller GitLab
Erfarenhet av testramverk som Robot Framework, Cucumber, PyTest, Behave el dyk
Mycket god svenska och engelska i tal och skrift
God vana av Git
Det är meriterande om du har erfarenhet av följande

Linux-distributioner
Vector CANoe/CANalyzer, dSpace
Powershell, Bash, Groovy, YAML
Utveckling eller test inom Automotive-branschen
Ansökan

Om du är intresserad av att bli en del av vår gemenskap på Infotiv så tycker vi att du ska ansöka till oss! Vi önskar höra mer om:

Dina erfarenheter; vad du har gjort tidigare i livet och vad du önskar göra framöver
Vem du är utanför arbetet
Eventuellt några rader om vad som gör dig till just den du är
Vilka vi är

Infotiv TechDev består idag av 70 ingenjörer, där våra uppdrag täcker alla aspekter av mjukvaruutvecklingsprocessen, från koncept och design till implementation och slutverifiering. Vi är även skickliga inom närbesläktade domäner, så som hårdvaruutveckling, systemdesign, data science, flödeskedjor (CI) och agila arbetssätt.

Vi värdesätter ett öppet klimat och stöttar våra ambitiösa medarbetare. Som medarbetare på Infotiv är man aldrig ensam. Man blir en del av ett företag som vårdar människorna som arbetar här och det finns flertalet aktiviteter att engagera sig i, både kompetensbyggande och sociala. Företaget karaktäriseras av korta beslutsvägar och en familjär atmosfär, vilket gör att din närmaste chef har stora möjligheter att själv bestämma. Ledorden Varmt hjärta, Skarp hjärna genomsyrar vår organisation och alla medarbetare. Givetvis har vi bra lön och kollektivavtal.

Låter detta intressant, så tveka inte att ansöka redan idag. Vi genomför intervjuer löpande och tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas innan sista ansökningsdatum. Vi hoppas att du vill vara med och växa med oss!

Title: Senior Data Analysis and Cyber Security Expert
Description:
Background
We help our customers modernize software application delivery to the cutting edge with Infrastructure as Code, containers, and private/public Cloud Computing. Today the majority of IT landscapes consist of static instances on Windows and Linux servers, with dependencies towards core applications still running on legacy hardware. At ICG we employ the experts that turn these old landscapes into an efficient and secure software delivery machine.
Together with Driven By Data, Innovation Capacity Group form a corporate group that combines our knowledge.
At Driven by Data, data is king and facts are unquestionable. We are a knowledge company active within the fields of operational intelligence, cybersecurity, and event-driven automation. Leveraging our expertise in these domains, we guide and advise our customers in their journey to become data-driven.
Profile
We are looking for a senior expert with experience from large corporations or authorities. You have a solid understanding of everything from networking to operating systems.
Besides the technical skills, you need to be an established consultant used to working in large-scale IT environments.
You have most likely worked in a computer emergency response team (CISRT), done penetration tests, or security advisory positions.
Skills
Security Information and Event Management (SIEM)
Vulnerability Management
AWS/Azure/GCP
Tensorflow, Keras, Jupyter m.fl.
Log and data tools such as ELK, Splunk, LogRythm or LogPoint
Time-series databases such as InfluxDB, Prometheus, Timestream or Druid
Python or other programming languages
Linux and Unix experience
Apache Airflow, Spark, Kafka, and/or Nifi
Experience in Machine Learning, Data Engineering, or Data Science is a plus.
What we offer you
We focus on the people. We aim to be the best Consultant Employer there is. Money and company growth are secondary to staff happiness, education, and knowledge sharing. We are built on a solid foundation of knowledge, sharing, and fun at work.
We expect all employees to be part of this culture.
Ask questions and be hungry for more knowledge
Hold seminars and attend national and international conferences
Arrange and take part in spontaneous activities
Come with us on our yearly international trips

Participation in our competence jam sessions, conferences, and trips

Title: Forward-deployed Data Engineer
Description:
Who We Are

Boston Consulting Group partners with leaders in business and society to tackle their most important challenges and capture their greatest opportunities. BCG was the pioneer in business strategy when it was founded in 1963. Today, we work closely with clients to embrace a transformational approach aimed at benefiting all stakeholders—empowering organizations to grow, build sustainable competitive advantage, and drive positive societal impact.

Our diverse, global teams bring deep industry and functional expertise and a range of perspectives that question the status quo and spark change. BCG delivers solutions through leading-edge management consulting, technology and design, and corporate and digital ventures. We work in a uniquely collaborative model across the firm and throughout all levels of the client organization, fueled by the goal of helping our clients thrive and enabling them to make the world a better place.

Practice Area Profile

BCG GAMMA combines innovative skills in computer science, artificial intelligence (AI), statistics, and machine learning with deep industry and functional expertise. The BCG GAMMA team is comprised of world-class data scientists, software and data engineers, as well as product experts with a consulting mindset.
We specialize in creating competitive advantage for our clients through AI driven transformations. Our teams own the full analytics value-chain end to end: framing new business challenges, designing innovative algorithms, implementing and deploying scalable solutions, and enabling colleagues and clients to fully embrace AI. Our product offerings span from fully custom-build to industry specific leading edge AI software solutions.

What You'll Do

As a forward-deployed Data Engineer, you’ll be part of our rapidly growing engineering team and help build the next generation of AI solutions. You’ll have the chance to partner with clients in a variety of BCG regions and industries, and on key topics like climate change, enabling them to design, build, and deploy new and innovative solutions. Additional responsibilities will include developing and delivering thought leadership in scientific communities and papers as well as leading conferences on behalf of BCG GAMMA.
WHO YOU ARE
We are looking for talented individuals with a passion for data engineering, software development and transforming organizations into AI led innovative companies
Apply data engineering practices and standards to develop robust and maintainable solutions
Actively involved in every part of the software development life cycle
Experienced at guiding non-technical teams and consultants in best practices for large-scale data engineering
Motivated by a fast-paced, service-oriented environment and interacting directly with clients on new features for future product releases
Enjoy collaborating in teams to share software design and solution ideas
A natural problem-solver and intellectually curious across a breadth of industries and topics



What You'll Bring (Experience & Qualifications)

Master’s Degree in Computer Science or relevant field
Experience in data engineering and working with global and remote agile squads
Proficiency with analytic software programming ideally in python, C++, or SCALA
Fluency with the storage, manipulation, and management of relational, non-relational and streaming data structures, specifically SQL, Spark, and Hadoop
Proficiency with infrastructure as code principles
Experience working on AWS, Azure, or Google cloud infrastructure
NICE TO HAVE
DevOps: Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD, Terraform
Understanding of parallel computing
Full stack development: GraphQL, React, JavaScript, TypeScript
Data Science and machine learning (Pandas, Scikit learn)
WORK ENVIRONMENT
Fluency in English is required as well as fluency in the local language for most locations
Ability to travel based on client and business needs. Expect 30-50%

Title: Solution Architect, Subject Matter Expert
Description:
Why We Work at Dun & Bradstreet
Dun & Bradstreet unlocks the power of data through analytics, creating a better tomorrow. Each day, we are finding new ways to strengthen our award-winning culture and accelerate creativity, innovation and growth. Our 6,000+ global team members are passionate about what we do. We are dedicated to helping clients turn uncertainty into confidence, risk into opportunity and potential into prosperity. Bold and diverse thinkers are always welcome. Come join us!

The main objective is to be the industry and subject matter expert within a specific area of Dun and Bradstreet’s portfolio. The Subject Matter Expert Solution Architect shall make it their main responsibility to learn the portfolio assigned by heart. Understand the USP and the Use cases where our solutions will be a great fit for our clients. The Subject Matter Expert will be responsible for developing high quality knowledge assets within the portfolio and will compose Solution Proposals for clients. Within their area, they shall support the Researchers in engaging with product teams and ensure that we capture the specifications accurately.
Additionally, the candidate shall take on responsibilities related to completing the BBC Migration. These responsibilities require knowledge of the BBC product, the data used, the meaning and the counterpart data within Data Blocks. Part of the migration work is also identifying use cases and target accounts that can be moved from BBC to the point of arrival product.
Key Responsibilities
Utilise your strategic and critical thinking abilities to investigate, and fulfill a business case requirement using a single DnB solution or a combination of products.
Self-manage, maintain documentation, management reporting and technical training
Analyze, plan and execute on BBC migration targets from November 2022 onwards until completion
Education/Experience and Competencies
7 + years of Experience in a relevant industry (data science, technology, commercial industries)
Demonstrate exceptional interpersonal skills and the ability to lead simultaneous projects for multiple customers
Showcase presentation skills to collaborate with Sales team & lead customers to a successful outcome
Experience with Business Requirements definition and management, structured analysis, process design, use case documentation
Presentation skills
PowerPoint, Excel, Work (MS Office)
Written and communication skills
Diplomacy
Business acumen
Persuasive
Can manage multiple projects and can handle multiple contact points

Education
University level - Business degree ideal
University level - Computer Science degree ideal

Prior Experience
Experience in a commercial role or customer service role
Experience with Business Requirements definition and management, structured analysis, process design, use case documentation
Worked with Bisnode Business Contacts and Presale, Implementation and customer service areas
Knowledge in the Master Data – Data Blocks
Global Recruitment Privacy Notice

Title: VP Engineering
Description:
At Airmee, we're working hard to create the best delivery experience in the world and optimise logistics to make it more efficient and environmentally sustainable. Our technology is at the heart of what we do, powering thousands of deliveries each day.

Airmee is one of Europe’s fastest growing logistics startups transforming last-mile delivery, backed by some of Sweden’s biggest investors and entrepreneurs. We help e-commerce by leveraging machine learning and powerful proprietary research-based technology to provide convenient and fast e-commerce deliveries same day or as fast as within the hour.

As the VP Engineering at Airmee, you will build and scale a world-class product engineering team of 20 engineers that is growing quickly each month as we expand with new services and internationally.

If you enjoy working in an entrepreneurial and rapidly-evolving environment, this role is for you.

About the role

This is a unique opportunity to have a central role at one of Europe’s fastest growing tech companies, making a wide impact on people’s everyday lives and disrupting one of the largest industries in the world. It is a role for you if you are interested in building a world-class next-generation tech team working with state-of-the-art technology. The role is also for someone that thrives in an ever-changing fast-paced environment where leadership is hands-on, and tasks can range from code reviews to setting product and development strategies.

Since we’re at the intersection of technology and the physical world, the stakes are higher. A whole new class of problems emerge as thousands of parcels and couriers are in motion every day. Problems that affect millions of people across our markets, and serve as opportunities to improve our services to make them as seamless as possible. Combined with exponential growth and the continuous launch of innovative services and features, the role therefore requires deep technical expertise and strong leadership skills.

It is a role that will work closely with the business and operations side of the company to create alignment with the engineers. A business mind-set is therefore crucial for the role. You cannot be a stranger to operating in fast-moving environments. Airmee’s high performance bar requires that you are self-motivated and target driven.

At Airmee, People primarily grow by working on challenging and innovative projects. As a leader, it is your job to empower them to do so and help solve any obstacles along the way.

A successful candidate will be highly analytical, resourceful, customer-focused, team-oriented, and have a natural ability to lead under time constraints to meet deadlines. We work on many products simultaneously, and a start-up mindset will be beneficial.

So what will you do?

Build a world-class tech team and be able to attract and retain talent. Our team is distributed across the world.
Deep dive leadership: able to understand our technical infrastructure in depth and evaluate engineers
Strategize and influence the product vision and roadmap in collaboration with the business and operations team
Collaborate with product, data science, engineering, business and operations teams to analyse key business problems and deliver engineering solutions end to end
Effectively work across the organisation and collaboratively with other teams
Translate the strategic roadmap into a practical execution plan with quarterly OKR's to ensure that we ship features faster at an unmatched speed
Build an influential culture of engineering excellence maintaining the balance and right trade-off for building products for speed and tech debt
Set up processes to handle ad hoc support requests from customers, sales, and logistics operations to make sure the general execution cycle is not disturbed
Develop an operational model to achieve operational excellence for the engineering and product teams
What're we looking for?

Proven experience building software across the stack (mobile, platform, etc.)
A minimum of 3 years of management building and leading a software engineering team in a fast-growing company/startup
Strong understanding of technical architecture, system design, and problem solving acumen on complex technical challenges
Willingness to dive deep and be hands-on
Proven experience working cross-functionally with Product Management, Data Science, and Business partners
Excellent written and verbal communication in English
Passion for high quality, usable, fast and reliable software
Exceptional work ethic
Masters degree or equivalent in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics or related field

Title: Älskar du att automatisera & skapa värde?
Description:
Vill du arbeta i en idérik miljö med fantastiska och prestigelösa kollegor som skapar smarta lösningar till den livsviktiga livsmedelsindustrin?
Vill du veta mer? Det hoppas vi..
Om tjänsten
Hej potentiella nya kollega! Om du börjar hos oss så kommer du att få arbeta i en agil modern organisation, där teamwork och kunden står i fokus.

Våra kunder är några av skandinaviens största livsmedelsföretag och våra projekt är roliga, utmanande och leder alltid till en förbättring på något sätt. Är du nyfiken på vad vi har förbättrat hittills? Vi har minskat matsvinn hos en kund och hos en annan har vi analyserat data från mjölkkornas mjölk för att korna ska må bättre.
Du blir..
..en del av vår familj och välkomnas till en arbetsplats där alla ser fram emot att gå till jobbet för vi har kul ihop, hjälper varandra framåt och är prestigelösa. Vi ligger på en 5:e plats på Great Place to Work listan och vi är ett jämställt gäng med 45% kvinnor och 55% män. Vi har högt till tak och nära till beslut, där vi värnar om vår personal. Hos oss får du möjligheten att arbeta med utvecklande och varierande uppdrag i en framtidsbransch. Du får en bra start hos oss med en mentor som hjälper dig att komma in i arbetet och ett genomarbetat onboardingprogram.

Om dig
Du är en nyfiken person som trivs med att finna lösningar, vågar göra fel och du är omtänksam och delar gärna med dig av kunskaper och erfarenheter för att öka ditt teams kunskaper. Du har tidigare erfarenhet från konsultrollen och gillar att ha kundkontakt. När det är mycket att göra så tappar du inte fokus och du ber om hjälp om du behöver. Du som alla andra vänner i teamet gillar teknik och utveckling och att kommunicera med kunder på svenska och engelska är inga problem för dig.
Din kompetens
Du har ett intresse och tidigare erfarenhet för att hjälpa kunder att effektiviera och förenkla med automationer. Tillsammans med ditt automationsteam kommer ni sätta er in i kundernas vardag och hjälpa dem att göra förbättringar i processer och se nya smarta möjligheter med automation. Vi utvecklar oftast i Python och RPA.
Rollen innebär också att arbeta över gränserna och med annan typ av utveckling som Data Science och med projektledning. Våra projekt är varierande och det kan vara både långa och korta projekt.

Om oss
Elvenite levererar hållbara lösningar för framtidens livsmedelsindustri. Mitt i hjärtat hos några av Skandinaviens ledande livsmedelsföretag kombinerar vi djupt bransch- och verksamhetskunnande med målet att maximera värdet av deras affärssystem och processer. Vi erbjuder dataanalyser och skapar datadrivna insikter och innovation, enkelt sagt, "vi gillar att göra livsmedelsindustrin smartare".
Vi söker dig som gör det du tror på, och är bra på det. Du är nyfiken, redo att utvecklas, vågar göra misstag och du har passion för att skapa förbättringar. Ta chansen och utvecklas med oss!
Det praktiska
1. Vi hoppas att du vill jobba på något av våra kontor i Stockholm, Göteborg eller Malmö
2. Arbetstid = 100%
3. Vi har fina förmåner och individuella löner
4. Vi vill ha dig så snart som möjligt eller efter årskiftet.
Sista ansökningsdag 21 December

Title: Game server developer
Description:
Tech-savvy programmer who love games? Then Thunderkick is your future romance!
As our new Game Server developer, you will sweat for creating kick-ass server-side game logic. Your day-to-day work can be anything from implementing game servers using java, improving our in-house frameworks or helping with game simulation and statistics.
At Thunderkick you will be a part of the whole development process, from concept to release party. You will be free from hierarchies, prestige and a department with only people doing the exact same thing as you. Our games are developed in small teams and your input and feedback are going to be important. As newly graduated- there is really no other place where you have the chance to grow as fast, where you get personal responsibility, and the potential to influence from day one.
What you will be doing
Design, implement and maintenance of Game Server Logic, Game Simulation, and Game Server Framework
Setup, release and deploy of game server and related artifacts
Game certification and documentation
“Scrum inspired” team-based game development
Brainstorming and evaluation of new game concepts
Game design and implementation
Lots and lots of table tennis (although not mandatory)
Who you are
Graduated from a data science program
Prestigeless and nice
Experience of working with Java
Understand both Swedish and English
Experience of Git, Gradle, Linux, SQL, Tomcat or similar is a plus

Title: Tjänsteansvarig IT infrastruktur
Description:
Tjänsteansvarig IT infrastruktur
Sista ansökningsdatum: 1 feb
Sveriges viktigaste IT-jobb, för klimatet
Sverige ska ställa om till förnybar el – och Svenska kraftnät har en avgörande roll.
För att klara det behöver vi nya digitala lösningar. Och fler smarta medarbetare som vill skapa dem. Hos oss kan du bli en viktig del av klimatomställningen genom att lösa svåra IT-utmaningar inom hela IT-kedjan – från infrastruktur till data science, AI och machine learning. Svenska Kraftnät söker dig som vill bibehålla och stärka organisationens viktiga IT-drift.
Om tjänsten
Som Tjänsteansvarig tillhör du avdelningen Infrastruktur och drift. Denna roll ansvarar för det övergripande och sammanhållande arbetet med förvaltning och vidareutveckling av våra IT-plattformar som är grundfundamentet för vår IT-drift. Vi har egna datacenter, plattformarna och tillhörande nät bygger på on-prem-lösningar.
Rollen som Tjänsteansvarig innebär att du kommer ha ett övergripande ansvar för driften och leveransen av våra IT-plattformar, som bygger på en kritisk infrastruktur med krav på drift 24/7.
Du kommer att tillhöra någon av enheterna som arbetar med infrastruktur och drift. I rollen ingår många kontaktytor, framförallt internt, men även externt i form av leverantörskontakter med mera. Samtidigt som du kommer att få jobba med flera spännande förändringsarbeten för att öka leveransförmågan så kommer du parallellt att jobba med vårt ständiga fokus på IT-säkerhet. Tjänsten är placerad på vårt huvudkontor i Sundbyberg men vi erbjuder möjlighet till distansarbete på upp till 50%.
Dina arbetsuppgifter
Leda förvaltningen och tjänsteleveransen genom att styra, planera och följa upp arbetet inom tjänsteområdet.
Samordna och styra interna och externa leverantörer.
Ansvara för tjänsteområdets backlogg och aktivitetslista.
Driva utvecklings och förbättringsåtgärder inom avdelningens ansvarsområden.
Administrera licenser och inköp kopplat till förvaltningen.
Din bakgrund
Vi lägger stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper och då rollen innebär att leda det operativa såväl som det taktiska arbetet inom tjänsteområdet söker vi dig som genom ett aktivt ledarskap involverar och stöttar teamet. Du är en kulturbärare med god tillit till dina kollegor samt med en god samarbetsförmåga. Som person är du en god kommunikatör och uttrycker dig väl på både svenska och engelska. Just nu drivs flera spännande förändringsarbeten och därför är det viktigt att du är utvecklingsorienterad och har ett strategiskt perspektiv.
Vi söker dig som har:
Akademisk utbildning med inriktning mot data/IT, systemvetenskap eller motsvarande kompetens erhållen på annat sätt
Minst fem års erfarenhet av att leda och ansvara för kritisk IT-infrastruktur.
Du har aktivt arbetat med etablerade IT-processer.
Att du jobbat med ekonomi, avtalshantering och leverantörsstyrning.
Det är meriterande om:
Du har erfarenhet av arbete inom IT-drift.
Du har erfarenheter av säkerhetsfrågor kopplade till IT-förvaltning.
Erfarenhet av att driva större förändringsprojekt som krävt både tekniska implementationer, samt förändringar i arbetssätt och kultur.
Certifiering inom minst ett projekt- och/eller en förvaltningsmetodik.
Vill du veta mer?
Vill du veta mer kontakta gärna rekryterande chef Anna Ljung, tel. nr. 010-4758769, alternativt ansvarig rekryterare Mats Jalmert, mats.jalmert@svk.se. Fackliga representanter är Emma Thornberg, SACO, tel. 010-475 84 77 och Mikael Hedenheim, ST, tel. 010-475 84 68. Du når oss också via e-post: fornamn.efternamn@svk.se.
Vi intervjuar kontinuerligt till denna tjänst.
Sista ansökningsdag
Välkommen med din ansökan senast den 18 januari 2023.
Vill du vara med och jobba i en IT-organisation där ditt arbete betyder någonting, på riktigt?
Vi är i dag ca 400 personer på IT och vi kommer att växa med ytterligare 140 personer kommande två år. Detta för att kunna skapa förutsättningar för Sverige att kunna fördubbla sin elproduktion och nå klimatmålen genom att helt ställa om till förnybar energi.
För att lyckas med målen så kommer vi använda oss av den senaste tekniken för att bland annat byta ut hela vår IT-infrastruktur samt öka vår utvecklingstakt kring system, digitalisering och processer. Allt utan att tumma på säkerheten förstås.
Om du skulle trivas att jobba och utvecklas i en växande organisation, och tillsammans med underbara medarbetare skapa en framåtlutad och robust IT-organisation, sök dig till oss!
Sveriges viktigaste IT-jobb hittar du här

Title: Remote Position - Experienced Consultants - Work/Life Balance
Description:
Remote Position - Experienced Consultants - Work/Life Balance
NFI - 15/12 AVW Mal_1671113825
This client is a newer group formed from an established organisation with offices across Sweden, as such you will be able to join a organisation with a fresh and exciting feel yet with the stability from the backing of an established organisation.

Here their focus is within Business Intelligence, Data Science and Automation and they are looking to add a BI Consultant to their team.This company recognises the growing market demand for data-driven solutions and wants you to join them on their journey to help their clients generate the most value from their data and meet their growing needs.

If BI isn't for you they're also looking to hire promising Data Engineers and Data Scientists to join their team, and wouldn't want to miss the opportunity if you think you would be the right fit. If so please enquire!

The interesting aspect about this role is that it is fully remote and even able to be worked from anywhere in Europe providing it's within 1 +/- time difference so there is no need or you to be located within Sweden for this role! Although this is a remote position this company has a excellent work culture which is cultivated through social activities and fikas which they have twice a day!

Their ambition here is to deliver full-scale projects and want their consultants to be a specialist in one field but require their consultants to have the ambition to learn something new and expand their technical knowledge.

For this role a successful candidate will have:

Significant experience in data and BI
Data modelling and analysis
Experience working with cloud solutions: Azure, AWS or GCP
Experience building dashboards and visualisations (Qlik or Power BI)
Experience working with customers, understanding their needs and meeting their demands

Bonus experience:

Consulting experience, or think you would be a good fit for this
Experience or desire to work in project management/ leadership

On a personal level, this company is looking for someone that can add to their happy work culture. You here will be granted freedom over your work, compensation, working hours and professional progression. Here you will thrive within an energetic environment that grants you autonomy over your work and work life.

What can they offer you?
