Title: Senior Software Architect – Cloud and Maps
Description:
Insights from the team
For Zenseact it is a given that software deployed to cloud is a key part of our product. To solve the problem of true autonomy we need to leverage the power of not only individual vehicles, but entire fleets. We are challenging traditional ways of working with software within automotive to create a modern and leading ecosystem of partners, data and end-user services around automated mobility.
Your Role
As a Software Engineer with architectural focus and capabilities within the cloud and maps product-domain, you will be a key person working with innovative connected features related to self-driving and advanced driver support. The role involves:
Creating and maintaining a high-level structure of our software system (architecture), its main components, their interactions and interfaces
Collaborating closely with delivery teams, architects, product owners, customers and other stakeholders
Establishing architectural visions and runways that guides the teams and serves as a basis for mutual understanding between all parties
Create designs supporting both functional needs as well as taking care of performance, resilience, reuse, maintainability, scalability and security
Supporting and leading teams in technical architecture work, specifically around cloud adoption

Your Profile
To be successful in this role you have a strong background in the full lifecycle of designing, developing, testing, deploying, operating and maintaining cloud based software solutions and managing individual project priorities, deadlines and deliverables. Furthermore you have:
Great communication and presentation skills
Experience building and operating large-scale systems in public cloud, specifically Microsoft Azure
Experience with architecture modelling
A self-starter with the ability to work effectively in teams and individually
Experience with any of this will give you an extra edge:
FuSa - Functional Safety (iso 26262 etc)
Operating global distributed system, especially including china
IoT or connected vehicle solutions
Stream analytics and processing technologies
Data science
Mapping and GIS
IT Security

Flexible-remote way of working: Zenseact has a flexible and modern approach, thus is happy to offer to its employees the possibility for a combination of work at the office and from home. This doesn't include fully remote work from outside Sweden/China.
More about Zenseact

Zenseact’s purpose is to make safe and intelligent mobility real, for everyone, everywhere. We develop the complete software stack for ADAS and AD, from sensing to actuation. Our focus is to build a single cutting-edge software platform in order to serve various levels of autonomy and offer unequaled scalability at the same time. We operate out of Gothenburg, Sweden and Shanghai, China. Zenseact’s first self-driving deployment will be launched on the next-generation vehicle platform from Volvo Cars.

Self-driving cars, when real, is estimated to reduce fatal car accidents with more than 85%, saving more than 50,000 persons from dying in car accidents caused by human errors each year. We feel that is a goal worth pursuing.

But technology, software, tools and datasets would not mean much without the best people behind the wheel to drive them. At Zenseact, some five hundred of the best engineering minds globally, stationed across two continents, are collaborating with the same passion: to bring autonomous driving to the streets for real and create a safer journey for everyone. This is part of our culture and how we work, develop and grow together.
Zenseact works proactively to create a culture of diversity and inclusion, where individual differences are appreciated and respected. To drive innovation we see diversity as an asset, which means we value and respect differences in gender, race, ethnicity, religion or other belief, disability, sexual orientation or age etc.

Interviews are held on a continuous basis, so we highly recommend that you submit your application at your earliest convenience.

Title: CX Solution Architect
Description:
To support our continuous growth, we're looking for a CX Solution Architect!
What is the job like, really?
As a CX Solution Architect, you're strongly committed to the customers' business issues and help them to find solutions that lead to smarter work and better customer satisfaction. You'll gain the customers' trust by seeing solutions instead of problems, with a smooth dialogue with architects, developers, product owners and other key people in the customer business organization. You'll also work with customers from an early stage of the sales dialogue and actively participate in presales. We're looking for fluent skills in both Swedish and English.
We tailor the role according to your expertise and are looking for a person who is keen to learn new areas and broaden their knowledge.
In addition to SAP CX, we work a lot with microservices, data science and machine learning, and hardcore ERP processes. We're also into other systems such as Salesforce and Microsoft – so there are plenty of opportunities to grow!
What are we looking for?
You're not just a PowerPoint architect, but you work hands-on with development
You can take the role of team lead and can be responsible for delivering quality
You keep yourself and your colleagues up-to-date with the latest news in relevant technologies
You work with the customers' architecture from early sales to go-live and continuous development
Cool, but what's in it for me?
Maximal flexibility and location independence – set up your workstation wherever you want and utilize our awesome offices’ premises in the way you feel is most suitable for you
Work-life balance – we encourage you to shape your work life according to your personal needs
More than generous employee benefits – lunch benefit, free snacks and drinks, healthcare and dental care services, extensive insurance, childcare services, freely selected work equipment and phones – the list goes on!
Competitive salary – your monthly salary base will be based on your experience and expertise + you’ll get to enjoy Vincit’s bonus model, personnel fund and transparent salary weeks
Competence development – we have set up Univincity to support workplace learning in various ways
Various career opportunities – take whatever career steps feel appropriate, whether shifting upwards, sideways or downwards.
Modern, transparent, and humane organization culture – thanks to these traits, we're an award-winning workplace to be proud of
Local and international work environment – enjoy the numerous activities and hobby clubs in your local community, go for an office exchange to our Lisbon office, or take a 2-year expat adventure to Vincit U.S.
A team of skilled experts at least equal to yourself – our way of working and thinking usually suits those who are, or want to be, at the top of their profession. Work with us, and you get to be part of our Vincit community which consists of the country’s top developers, designers, and other experts.
Curious but still on the fence?
If there’s anything you’d like to chat about the job, don’t hesitate to get in touch with us. To get to know us as an employer, we recommend checking our career site, blog, Facebook, Instagram and LinkedIn.
P.S. Please note that if you live abroad and want to work with us, you need to have the necessary permits for working in Sweden.
Job Type: Full-time

Title: Testledare
Description:
Är du en erfaren testledare som är redo att ta nästa steg?

Vi på Infotiv söker dig som har varit i en större industriell eller offentlig miljö i flera år, och som vet hur mjukvaruprodukter, med hög kvalitet, tar sig hela vägen från specifikation till produktion.

Hur berättar man för tunga stakeholders att kvaliteten behöver förbättras, utan att trampa någon på tårna? Det vet du! I tjänsten kommer du att få använda både dina tekniska kunskaper och dina personliga egenskaper, och du får hos Infotiv möjligheten att bli en nyckelspelare i våra kunders resa in i framtidens mjukvaruutveckling. Som teknikkonsult på Infotiv står du och dina kunskaper i centrum, och tillsammans tar vi din karriär till nya höjder.

Infotiv är en ingenjörsbyrå med 25 år i branschen och med moderna ambitioner för framtiden. Infotivs affärsområde TechDev ligger i framkant när det kommer till tekniker inom bl a mjukvaruutveckling, testsystem och arbetsmetodik. Detta i kombination med vårt varma hjärta och skarpa hjärna är bestående framgångsfaktorer för oss. Vi nöjer oss inte med att uppfylla förväntningarna, utan vill överträffa dem varje gång.

Din framtida utmaning

Som testledare har du ansvar för bland annat testplanen och de verifieringsaktiviteter som behöver genomföras. Du kan förutse var riskerna finns i systemet och tar höjd för dessa i planeringen. Du vet att skriva kod endast är halva jobbet, och vill göra övriga organisationen medveten om detta. Till din hjälp har du din solida övertygelse, dina sociala färdigheter och en rejäl dos envishet. I gengäld kommer du få en vardag som ständigt förser dig med nya erfarenheter.

Den du är idag

Som person är du engagerad och strävar efter att leverera ditt bästa resultat varje gång. Du är kreativ och nyfiken inför uppdragets behov och kan snabbt anpassa dig till olika situationer. Du tycker att det är spännande när allting inte är bestämt på förhand och sporras av att få sätta dig in i nya sammanhang. Du har fenomenal fingertoppskänsla och har förståelse för projektets behov, för att kunna hitta den rätta lösningen för att komma framåt.

Vi lägger stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper!

För att vara framgångsrik i rollen ser vi att du:
Krav

Har minst 3 års erfarenhet, som testledare inom mjukvaruutveckling
Har erfarenhet av agila utvecklingsmetodiker och tillhörande kvalitetsarbete
Har erfarenhet av att arbeta med teststrategier, testrapportering och planering.
Vill jobba som ledare i en komplicerad mjukvarumiljö
Vi ser med intresse på om du har något av följande erfarenheter med dig

Jobbat med större IT-system
Designat testfall på system- eller komponentnivå
Erfarenhet av testarbete i en korsfunktionell miljö
Erfarenhet av att hålla kurser i testning
Erfarenhet av att hålla föredrag om testning
ISTQB-certifierad
Ansökan

Om du är intresserad av att bli en del av vår gemenskap på Infotiv så tycker vi att du ska ansöka till oss! Vi önskar höra mer om:

Dina erfarenheter; vad du har gjort tidigare i livet och vad du önskar göra framöver
Vem du är utanför arbetet
Eventuellt några rader om vad som gör dig till just den du är
Vilka vi är:
Infotiv TechDev består idag av 70 ingenjörer, där våra uppdrag täcker alla aspekter av mjukvaruutvecklingsprocessen, från koncept och design till implementation och slutverifiering. Vi är även skickliga inom närbesläktade domäner, så som hårdvaruutveckling, systemdesign, data science, flödeskedjor (CI) och agila arbetssätt.

Vi värdesätter ett öppet klimat och stöttar våra ambitiösa medarbetare. Som medarbetare på Infotiv är man aldrig ensam. Man blir en del av ett företag som vårdar människorna som arbetar här och det finns flertalet aktiviteter att engagera sig i, både kompetensbyggande och sociala. Företaget karaktäriseras av korta beslutsvägar och en familjär atmosfär, vilket gör att din närmaste chef har stora möjligheter att själv bestämma. Ledorden Varmt hjärta, Skarp hjärna genomsyrar vår organisation och alla medarbetare. Givetvis har vi bra lön och kollektivavtal.

Låter detta intressant, så tveka inte att ansöka redan idag. Vi genomför intervjuer löpande och tjänsten kan komma att tillsättas innan sista ansökningsdatum. Vi hoppas att du vill vara med och växa med oss!

Title: We are recruiting a Tech Lead to Modelon, Lund!
Description:
Modelon is forming a new team in Lund for developing a new web app to intuitively set-up simulation and optimization experiments and visualize big data for decision making. Therefore, we need to recruit an experienced Tech Lead to set-up and lead this team.
Modelon has already developed a web app for building models and a backend for performing simulations on the cloud called Modelon Impact : This will be complemented by the experimentation web app that is targeted to a larger user category not involved in creating models but involved in using models to make model-based product design decisions.
The new web app will enable running thousands of simulations in order that our users can find the optimal selection of components and parametrization of their new product offers. Our users typically work with designing sustainable energy, automotive and aerospace solutions, i.e., wind power plants, solar power plants, carbon-capture technology, electric cars, and electric airplanes. They want to perform post processing of simulation results, Monte Carlo simulations, sensitivity analysis, optimizations, machine learning training, etc. The users need a convenient way to define workflows to simplify repetitive work. The vision includes being able to perform such tasks also from tablets and smart phones.
What will you do?
The work of the team involves defining the appropriate architecture and tool chain. Furthermore, feature design and UI design will be performed together with product management and with inputs from Modeldon's service and commercial departments and from customers. The work involves collaboration with modeling web app and backend teams to provide a coherent UX.
The work in the team will involve technologies such as ECMAScript, TypeScript, Python, PWA, RWA, React, data science, statistics, optimization, Plotly, 3D visualization, machine learning and Jenkins.
Ensure the delivery of our projects: It's a hands-on role so we expect you do development and code reviews. While full-time development is not part of the role, we encourage you to take part in the development activities of your choosing to keep your skills updated.
Collaborate closely with the Product Manager, Team Leads and Scrum Master, to make sure our projects are delivered efficiently and following our standards and best practices.
Nurture and assess developers assigned to you: Encourage curiosity and continuous learning in the area you are an expert in.
Provide insights to and collaborate closely with the CTO to improve the engineering skills of the team. Coordinate activities between all engineering areas.
Required skills and qualifications
5 years or more of professional development experience.
Experience in TypeScript, Python and React.
Prior experience as Team Lead/Tech Lead/Architect is a plus.
Enjoy working on challenging solutions and systems.
Believe that building great applications is not only about delivering code that "works", but involves thinking about reusability, maintainability, security, and performance.
Curious, structured, with a "Can do attitude" and a product mindset.
Enjoys collaboration within the team and with other departments.
Good at communicating in both Swedish and English.
Meritorious skills
Experience of Agile development and practices.
Jenkins, ECMAScript, PWA, RWA, data science, statistics, optimization, 3D Visualization and machine learning.
About Modelon
Modelon offers systems modeling and simulation software that accelerates product innovation, development, and operations in a range of industries. We believe that we can only achieve excellence when we work together. Our teams are closely aligned, and we encourage cross-team collaboration at every opportunity. Modelon is revolutionizing the engineering design industry by offering technologies and services that enable customers to leverage system simulation. Modelon's flagship product, Modelon Impact, is a cloud system simulation platform that helps engineers virtually design, analyze, and simulate physical systems. Our team brings deep industry expertise and is dedicated to guiding our customers in creating innovative technologies at their respective organizations. Headquartered in Lund, Sweden, Modelon is a global company with offices in Germany, India, Japan, Prague, and the United States. Read more about us here:
Contact and Information
In this recruitment, Modelon collaborates with Experis IT, with extensive experience in recruiting specialists and managers within IT. For questions about the position, please contact recruitment consultant Jenny Flygare, jenny.flygare@se.experis.com , 070-2557143 or Luka Jovovic, luka.jovovic@se.experis.com 072-2058887. You apply for the position via the application link at www.experis.se .
Welcome with your application!

Title: Cyber Security Engineer
Description:
Working with Cyber Security means covering methods, tools, technologies and software

architectures to ensure a strong level of Cyber security.
Be a part of a network of technical specialists and architects with different domain expertise,e.g personal security, data science, software engineering.

Support the ART’s management team with cybersecurity competence as a speaking partner.

Support the ART’s technical roles (e.g., Development Teams, Architects) with competence regarding cybersecurity.

Support ART’s technical roles (e.g., Development Teams, Architects) with cybersecurity development- and V&V- activities, but then always as a temporary team member, i.e., the responsibility for the work products always remains with the owning team.

Support the ART’s quality assurance by participating in verification reviews with a cybersecurity

perspective.

Support the ART’s cybersecurity related sourcing (CS-SOW), evaluation of supplier’s cybersecurity

work and achievement of cybersecurity (CS-JR).
Act as a cybersecurity contact person for the Solution/ART.

cybersecurity.

Title: Data Engineer / Data Scientist till Preem
Description:
Nu har du möjlighet att bli pionjär i Preems nyligen etablerade dataplattform och skapa värde för verksamheten och omvärlden genom data. Haka på deras digitala transformation och bli en viktig del i resan mot en grönare framtid. Vi söker en Data Engineer / Data Scientist med passion för problemlösning och intresse för Databricks, Machine Learning och Big Data.

Om rollen

I rollen som Data Engineer / Data Scientist kommer du få vara en del av Preems storsatsning till att höja datakvalitén och bli mer datadrivna. Du kommer ha en central roll i att utveckla och implementera initiativ kopplat till data. Arbetet rör ett framväxande funktionsområde inom företaget och det finns stort utrymme att ingå i de arkitekturella frågeställningarna och besluten.

Du kommer vara en del i ett team tillsammans med utvecklare, lösnings- och informationsarkitekter vars uppgifter är att säkerställa en kontrollerad och fungerande helhet gällande IT-arkitektur, Information Management och Masterdata Management.

Huvudsakliga arbetsuppgifter:
Bygga och underhålla den koncerngemensamma dataplattformen (Databricks i Azure)
Optimera data pipelines
Möjliggöra snabb och pålitlig dataåtkomst
Utföra avancerade analyser av data för att hitta mönster och generera insikter för att fatta bättre affärsbeslut
Etablera, utveckla och förvalta machine learning
Du blir en viktig del av Preem - en arbetsplats som präglas av välkomnande stämning, förtroende för medarbetarna och ambitionen att vara bäst i branschen när det gäller hållbarhet. Här får du frihet under ansvar och ofta chansen att vara med under hela processen - från början till slut. Ansvarstagande, nyskapande och inkluderande värderas högt på Preem och genomsyrar allt arbete. Därför är det viktigt att du delar samma uppfattning.

Rollen är en heltidstjänst till Preems huvudkontor i Stockholm. Preem har en hybrid work-model där du kan arbeta på distans hälften av din arbetstid. Du rapporterar till chefen för Digital, BI & Governance.

Är det här du?

Vi söker dig som är en passionerad problemlösare med intresse för att använda data för att lösa affärsproblem och förbättra verksamheter. Vi ser gärna att du arbetet med Azure Databricks, Machine Learning och Big Data-teknologier.

För att lyckas i rollen är det viktigt att du har god samarbetsförmåga, är initiativtagande och har ett flexibelt förhållningssätt. Vi kommer att lägga stor vikt vid dina personliga egenskaper.

Du har:
Erfarenhet av att jobba med Data Engineering och/eller Data Science
Goda kunskaper i programmering, särskilt i SQL och Python med tillhörande bibliotek och ramverk
God konceptuell förståelse för maskininlärning
Erfarenhet av DevOps-processer
Bekantskap med olika databaser och datalagringssystem
Akademisk examen inom datavetenskap, statistik, matematik eller liknande
Meriterande:
Erfarenhet av att arbeta tillsammans med kravställare på data för BI- och OI-rapportering
Insikt i de arkitekturella vägval som är aktuella i implementationen av en dataplattform med Lakehouse-struktur
Fördjupad förståelse av maskininlärning
Databricks och relaterade verktyg
Big Data-teknologier
MLOps och CI/CD
Rollen kräver att man kan kommunicera obehindrat i tal och skrift både på svenska och engelska.

Intresserad av att ansöka eller få veta mer?

I denna rekrytering samarbetar Preem med IDG Recruitment. Vid intresse eller frågor kontakta Moa Eriksson, Rekryteringskonsult på 070 828 36 65, moa.eriksson@idg.se eller Maria Widegren, Rekryteringskonsult 073 423 15 50, maria.widegren@idg.se

För att ansöka, vänligen skicka in ditt CV eller ansök med Linkedin.

Om Preem

Vi är Preem, Sveriges största drivmedelsbolag. Vi har en vision om att leda omvandlingen mot ett hållbart samhälle genom att bli klimatneutrala i hela värdekedjan, från utvinning av råvaror till produktion och försäljning. Senast år 2030 ska Preem producera 5 miljoner kubikmeter förnybara drivmedel, och senast 2035 ska vi vara klimatneutrala i hela värdekedjan. Preems raffinaderier räknas till de mest moderna och miljöanpassade i Europa med en raffineringskapacitet på över 18 miljoner kubikmeter per år. Vår verksamhet omfattar produktion, försäljning, distribution samt trading och varuförsörjning. Vi förädlar och säljer drivmedel, eldnings- och smörjolja samt andra produkter till företag och privatpersoner. Vi har ett rikstäckande servicenät med drygt 520 tankställen för privat- och yrkestrafik. Preem AB har drygt 1 500 anställda varav 950 arbetar vid raffinaderierna. För helåret 2020 var Preems omsättning 68,2 miljarder SEK.

Title: Embedded Software Developer
Description:
I am Peter, your potential next leader. I know a lot about cows, not because I have a double degree in Data Science and applied mathematics but because I have worked 17 years with robots and milk production at DeLaval. So a couple of years ago, I thought to myself, what is beyond robots, cows, and milk? And I found my way in consultancy, and now I'm stuck in the world of exploring new things! My team at Knightec and I get the opportunity to create products needed in the market designed to be sustainable for customers who value our competence. Right now, I'm focusing on Electrification. I'm too humble to say that I'm an expert, but I have great experience in the field! I love the technical aspects of my work, creating, modifying, and developing products. But the best part of my day is to discuss, learn and mentor my team members to have the best chance to find their following context or projects. I appreciate open dialogues and transparency to give you situational leadership; that is one thing I can promise you!
Why working as a consultant will fit you
Because you want to focus on solving technical problems without internal politics, you want to make new products that last, not handling the old legacy. And you want to have a team with engineers who understand the problem you meet and help you see them from another perspective.
What will you work with?
As an embedded developer in our team in Stockholm, you will work on meaningful projects. You will be working within product and service development for great Swedish technology clients. And be a significant driver shifting towards a more sustainable world.
We believe that a holistic approach is required to make products and services succeed, both now and in the future. That's why we work within six fields of opportunities where your and our expertise can make an impact. Our way of working is in cross-functional teams, and the hands-on work is often in creating software and solutions from a low level to a high level. That means that you will have the chance to work within teams that focus on autonomous, connected and safe and secure, for example, within electromobility, connectivity, and development platforms.

What you need to bring
Experience in product development and lifecycle of a new project
Programming, such as C, C++, or Java
Experience from working in cross-functional teams
Knightec
We are consultants in technology, digitalization, and leadership. We work to improve people's lives through game-changing solutions. We are engineers focusing on product development that should be sustainable and durable in edge technology in both in-house projects and at customer sites. We are more than 900 engineers in 10 different cities. To be a consultant at Knightec isn't just a job; it is the way to build a career that you can be proud of!

Title: Automotive Software Test Engineer
Description:
Personality / Commitment
At ALTEN in Gothenburg, Sweden we work with some of Sweden’s largest automotive manufacturers within research and development. Now we are looking to expand our team of automotive software test engineers. Within the field of testing, the trend is moving towards automation. Therefore, we are looking for you who are an automotive software test engineer or automotive software developer, preferably experienced with Python and Continuous Integration (CI/CD). Here, we encourage and support our engineers to evolve professionally as personally. Therefore, you will have the fullest support from your closest ALTEN manager, who will follow you in your journey and support you forward – in the direction you want. When you feel like you want to learn something new, you can always take it into your own hands because ALTEN Academy offers several educations, from new programming languages to negotiation skills and much more.
Job / Skills
To be successful in this role, we believe that you have:
Minimum 5 years of experience working with automotive software, either testing or development.
Professional experience working with Python or C++.
Worked in an Agile environment.
A relevant degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Electronics, Data Science, Mathematics, Physics or similar.
Meritorious experience:
Experience in PyTest or Robot Framework.
Experience with CI/CD tools e.g. Jenkins.
Experience with Vector tools e.g. CANoe, CANalyzer.
Experience with CAN, LIN, Ethernet.
To succeed in the role as a consultant at ALTEN you need to be analytical, have a great sense for quality, a positive attitude and you need to be a team-player. If You find this as an interesting next step and would like to get in touch with us, don’t hesitate to send in your application.
About ALTEN
ALTEN is one of Europe’s largest technology and IT consulting companies with over 45,000 employees in over 30 countries. Our engineers carry out complex and highly technical projects throughout the value chain of the most prestigious companies in all sectors, such as Automotive, Telecom, Industry, Energy, Aerospace & Defense and Life Science. In Sweden, we are over 1300 committed employees with 11 offices in 10 cities - from Lund in the south to Skellefteå in the north.
For the fourth year in a row, ALTEN has been named one of Sweden's most attractive employers by Karriärföretagen 2023, an award for employers that offer unique career and development opportunities.
Welcome to read more about us at alten.se
We are looking forward to your application!

Title: E-MOBILITY – SYSTEM ENGINEER – REQUIREMENT MANAGEMENT
Description:
E-MOBILITY – SYSTEMS ENGINEER, REQUIREMENT MANAGEMENT
MBE are expanding and are looking for a senior creative and curious SYSTEM ENGINEER / E-mobility developer. Preferably with experience from development of ESS (Energy storage systems), Charging systems, Electrical machines and Power conversion in 400/600V or higher, and 24/48V systems.
Our customers are developing the future technology for ever more environmentally beneficial machines, such as full electric drivelines for road transport, marine and/or construction machinery. They are facing an intensive period to develop a new technical platform for E-mobility.
If you are driven to contribute with your qualified skills for development and implementation of tomorrow’s technical solutions, we have the challenges for you.
For the right candidates we can also offer the opportunity to work in exciting establishment projects supported by expert panels from Swedish authorities within AI and energy storage systems in industries, household and transport sector such as EV Charging and ESS systems for vehicles and Smart Energy Storage System Development. We want to make it easier for our customers to take responsibility for the climate with joint technological development as well as applying MBE’s advanced technical innovations in AI and ESS. More info at “Smart Energy Storage System development, SMARTERGY”
SYSTEMS ENGINEER, E-MOBILITY
Electromobility is one of the most important development areas for the climate and society today.
Mutual Benefits Group (founded 2008) started Smartergy AB, 2020 and are responsible for several research projects within ELECTRIC GRID POWER BALANCING and AI to provide society with better energy systems to E-mobility, Industry and Household sector. The projects are financed by The Swedish Energy Agency (Energimyndigheten), VGR, ALMI and Mutual Benefits Group.
When joining the Energy Storage System engineering (ESS) team you will not only develop the interior challenges of ESS but also the ESS and Charging of vehicles on the field. It means distributed AI balanced and mixed ESS, to support the electric grid as well as the Electric Vehicles charging demand (up to 1200 kW) balanced with Industry and Household electric energy demands.
Together with our clients we prepare and develop the conditions for the transition from conventional powertrains to electromobility and secure a stepwise implementation in different segments/regions.
In this project we develop and drive the electromobility product portfolio for Heavy Duty & Public transport vehicles as well as creating opportunities for neighbouring business areas within Electromobility in the vehicles as well as the infrastructure on the field. The importance of electromobility is growing every day and a key component within the electrified powertrain is the Energy Storage System.
Smartergy AB are the product owner and are accountable for the lifecycle management of the ESS, from advanced engineering, throughout product development into the maintenance phase.
WORK DESCRIPTION, E-MOBILITY REQUIREMENT MANAGER, ENERGY STORAGE SYSTEMS
To the Automotive Energy Storage System Engineering (ESS) team we are now recruiting two REQUIREMENT MANAGERS.
Mutual Benefits Engineering AB (MBE), Energy Storage System engineering is a growing agile driven organization in place to shape the future! Our ESS team are responsible to develop the complete ESS functionality realized by HW and SW solutions. The team consist of an agile and innovative driven organization with skilled product developers consisting of passionate people from all disciplines included in ESS such as Energy engineering (BMS, SW, Electro chemistry, Power Electronics) Data Science (AI), and Project managers.
We work in an optimistic atmosphere, where care of society, joy, knowledge sharing and openness are key characteristics. With us, you will have a diverse, top skilled, friendly and innovative driven team on your side, always providing you the help needed to manage tasks you cannot imagine today. We are working in a cross-functional way from requirement, concept and design, final verification, implementation in production and aftermarket. To secure commonality and an efficient product portfolio we need to support the ESS organization with direction and decision material.
REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS:
You are an experienced engineer who easily introduces yourself to new technologies. We look forward to having at least 5 years of industrial experience from design, testing and verification, combined with sound theoretical knowledge. We believe you like to have structure, order and proactivity in your work. The ability to work as a team player independently in teams, give and interact with others and that you are communicative and driven are qualities that we highly appreciate for these assignments.
We believe that to be successful in this position, you are a pragmatic team player that loves to develop System designs with the customer in focus.
Since the area is in an early phase, it is important that you are flexible and enjoy working in a changing environment.
You have a broad knowledge and experience in system engineering including Electrical, Mechanical and functional development.
We believe you need to have solid experience in our clients toolchain and processes regarding requirement and product documentation/logic such as KOLA, Dim RM, SE Tool etc.
Master of Science in Mechatronics, Electrical or Mechanical engineering.
5 years’ experience from quality and system engineering within automotive systems.
Solid experience in requirement balancing and alignment between customers and stakeholders.
Experience from working with the requriement tools System weaver (SE-Tools) or Dimensions-RM.
Proven record of excellent communication and presentation skills.
MERITORIOUS EXPERIENCE:
It is considered a merit if you have experience within one or several of the following: Experience within Energy Storage Systems. Charging systems, Electrical machines or Power conversion in 400/600V or higher. Agile Principals and methods.
ABOUT MBE
ADVANCED TECHNOLOGY AND MANAGEMENT
MBE have solid experience of sustainable product development in Automotive and Clean Energy Tech industry. After awards for growth and leadership such as DI Gazelle with successful international business we celebrated our 10th anniversary 2018.
We created and developed our distinguished leadership model together with professors at IHM Personal Leadership program and Stephen R Covey’s methodology. You will recognize many similarities in Simon Sinek’s visions. The model is continuously sharpened since 2001.
VERSATILE & INCLUSIVE TEAM
We are happy to see applications from creative, curious and senior developers to join our expert team towards advanced technology clients within Automotive and Circular Energy. We are extra happy to see applications from FEMALE applicants.
We engage top engineers. Experienced experts as well as distinguished Newly graduated engineers with personal values for Sustainable Engineering, IT and Embedded solutions, caring for a well balanced life with family & fun together with YOUR best career development!
3D CAREER PLAN
Successful companies build a well-planned business plan. MBE builds successful people through their individual “Personal Business Plan”! Since we have a wide palette of recognized international clients and assignments, there’s always a matching assignment connecting to YOUR career plan.
Through the MBE’s solid leadership model, our employees develop their career in 3D! Through long-term planning, between the 3D parts Work, Health and Social life, together with challenging assignments, important contacts and supplementary courses to become the best they can be… with their own individual prerequisites!
APPLY, DEVELOP AND CREATE YOUR FUTURE!
We hope you find this attempting to be a part of! Join us on the travel to YOUR best future! Apply, Develop and Create Your Future! Now!
Send your application as soon as possible to jobb@mutualbenefits.se
Name your application to “E-MOBILITY ESS RM”

Title: AI-utvecklare
Description:
Önskar du också att du kunnat säga att du var med i Spotifys linda, eller att du bidragit till koden bakom PayPal? Nu har du chansen. Vi har tekniken. Vill du vara med och demokratisera den tillsammans med oss?
Nu söker vi Utvecklare som är extremt nyfiken på AI till vårt utvecklingsteam i Halmstad och vill gärna träffa dig som:
Är en van programmerare som har börjat gräva lite i AI och hur man kan integrerar olika AI-lösningar och hur man kan skapa affärsnytta av dessa.
Har väldigt goda kunskaper i såväl svenska som engelska i både tal och skrift. All kommunikation och dokumentation sker på de språken.
Men viktigast av allt är att du har ett stort intresse för teknik, maskininlärning och artificiell intelligens

Det är meriterande om du även har:
Erfarenhet av OpenAI
God erfarenhet av klassiska databaser
Erfarenhet som programmerare / systemutvecklare.
Bakgrund inom Data Science
Erfarenhet av Tensorflow, Tensor RT, PyTorch och/eller liknande AI-verktyg

Som AI-utvecklare hos Effektify kommer du jobba med en bredd i hela kedjan från idé till färdig AI-lösning. Du kommer arbeta till stor del med vårt team som utvecklar vår plattform där ni samarbetar och delar kunskap för att hitta nya innovativa lösningar. Målet är att du ska axla rollen som AI-specialist i teamet. För denna roll värderar vi personliga egenskaper högre än erfarenhet.
Utöver dina professionella kvaliteter värdesätter vi att du
Är lösningsorienterad och driven
Har god samarbetsförmåga och värderar teamets gemensamma mål
Är öppen för att prova på nya tekniker och lämnar alltid koden i ett bättre skick än du fann den

Du erbjuds
Möjlighet att vara delaktig i en spännande resa på ett växande techbolag
En flexibel och trivsam arbetsplats på ett modernt kontor som är något alldeles extra, med allt från spelhörnor till loungeavdelning

Om Effektify
Effektify är en plattform för att effektivisera företags marknadsföring.
Nu går vi in i en mycket spännande fas för att vidareutveckla, skala upp och samtidigt lansera fler spännande tjänster i vår plattform. Därför söker vi nu dig som intresserad av att utmana, utveckla och ser nya förbättrade lösningar för framtiden tillsammans med vårt utvecklingsteam!
Bakgrund
Bolaget grundades våren 2021 och har huvudkontor centralt i Halmstad. Vi har idag även ett nyöppnat kontor i Berlin och totalt är vi 22 personer.
Effektify består av två affärsområden där den ena delen är utveckling och den andra delen består av vår konsultverksamhet med specialister och experter inom analys, strategi och drift av digital marknadsföring.
Övrig information om tjänsten
Start: Enligt överenskommelse
Omfattning: Heltid
Placering: Centrala Halmstad

Vi går igenom urvalet löpande och annonsen kan stängas ner innan tjänsten är tillsatt om vi gått över till urvals- och intervju fasen.
Skicka din ansökan tillsammans med ditt CV till jobs@effektify.com
För mer information om alla våra lediga tjänster gå till https://effektify.com/karriar/

Title: Senior BI Analyst (Stockholm, Sweden)
Description:
As Google Cloud's premier partner in AI, we provide world-class businesses with cutting-edge data solutions in the cloud. We help clients take leading technology to the limits by combining our expertise in machine learning, data engineering, and analytics. With Google Cloud as our foundation, we help businesses future-proof their solutions, deepen their understanding of consumers, increase competitive advantage and unlock operational efficiencies.

Our team consists of experts in machine learning, data science, software engineering, mathematics, and design. We share a passion for data & analysis, operate at the cutting edge, and believe in a pragmatic approach to solving hard problems.
THE ROLE
You will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining analytics solutions, with a primary focus on business unit-specific data marts, self-service data models, building front-end analytical visualisations/reports (typically Looker), and training business users.
You will help deploy analytical data models, advise clients on development, and conduct co-development sessions to share your knowledge with customers. Being able to understand what technologies make a BI function a success; you will also have a good understanding of data warehouse technology on offer such as BigQuery and Snowflake.
This job is perfect for an individual who loves sharing their technical knowledge with others in a hands-on manner, thrives on working with different clients in just about every industry and proactively contributes to the open-source community.
As a Senior BI Analyst you will work alongside:
Analytics engineers: Responsible for designing, building, and maintaining end-to-end business intelligence solutions, with a primary focus on enterprise-wide data warehouse design, data models, and storage optimisation. Typically with DBT, snowflake/Bigquery and Google Cloud.
Architects: Responsible for designing the solution and data architectures. data architects design the end-to-end business intelligence solutions with a focus on designing the most optimal data model and architecture solution.
Data Engineers: Responsible for building applications which connect systems, collect data, process that data into a useful format. Often this data is ‘big’ and requires distributed frameworks to move and process. A data engineer is a key cog in a data platform as they look after the acquisition of data for analytics, and connecting the output of analytics to operational systems.
Your responsibilities will include:
Platform implementations:
Design and Build self service business intelligence platforms (usually Looker)
Build unit-specific data marts using dbt
Gain a deep understanding of the Looker Platform and Google Bigquery
Gain a understanding of the wider modern data stack
Work with analytics Engineers who design big data warehouses and advise on infrastructure decisions
Insights for Clients:
Produce actionable and insightful visualisations and dashboards from large, complex datasets in many different fields
Gather requirements of businesses challenges and enable them to make better decisions by analysing data and storytelling
Collaboration:
Share your knowledge of these tools through co-development and training sessions for clients
Work in a collaborative way with our customers and other team members
Actively propose solutions to fulfil our customer’s goals and requirements
Work closely with our tech partners: Google Cloud, Looker, Snowflake,dbt, fivetran.
Requirements
Essential:
Experience with Looker and/or Tableau or similar leading BI tools
Experience in the Google Cloud, AWS or Azure environment
Proficiency in SQL & GIT
Experience translating business requirements into technical solutions
Ability to communicate complex ideas in a simple way to a wide range of audiences
Proven analytical and problem-solving skills
Experience in a client-facing position, ideally in a BI consultancy
Bonus Points:
Previous experience with Looker, dbt, Snowflake or BigQuery
Experience in CI/CD principles
Benefits
The Basics: 30 days holiday in addition to bank holidays, Private Occupational Pension (Salary Sacrifice), Team Bonus payable annually.
Health & Wellness: 4500 kr Private Health Insurance Allowance per year, 5000 kr Wellness Allowance per year, Employee Assistance Program

Learning: 8500 kr Conference Budget + 4 days attendance per year, Access to Linux Academy, Coursera, and LinkedIn Learning
Career Development: A personalised development plan to ensure you hit your professional goals with a clear roadmap for progression
Impact: The opportunity to work on cutting-edge AI and ML solutions spanning multiple industries and with market-leading organisations
Innovation: Access to Datatonic LABs, our Research & Development hub. Experiment and bring forward ideas, create impactful and meaningful work in a creative and collaborative environment - even just for fun!
Flexible Working: A mix of office and remote working, 1200 kr Home Equipment Allowance
Team Vibe & Social: A welcoming and friendly team plus weekly Team Lunches and Monthly Social Events

WORKING FOR DATATONIC
We’re an eclectic team with lots of different interests and personalities. We have many different roles across data science, engineering, analytics, consulting, marketing, business development, and operations. We have offices in the UK, Stockholm, Geneva, Munich, and Barcelona, and we work with clients in many other European countries. We allow for flexible working hours and the possibility of remote work.
As a company, we have a strong emphasis on learning and professional development. Our core values are:

Cultivating Excellence
A hub for continuous learning, curiosity, developing ideas, testing things out - and then putting ‘excellence’ into practice.
Owning It
Working collaboratively in cross-functional teams to achieve customer delight. We love what we do and draw immense satisfaction from taking responsibility and seeing the results of our work.
Purposeful Impact
Creating positive change for our customers, using the most relevant machine learning and analytics approaches and the best technologies to meet real business needs.
Winning with Partners & Friends
Our business has been built on great partnerships and open-source collaboration. It’s one thing to be successful, but to do it in partnership with great people and other great companies is even better in our opinion.
Datatonic is committed to being an equal opportunities employer. Diversity, equity and inclusion are a key part of our values and central to our overall mission of recruiting, retaining and promoting a diverse mix of colleagues. We encourage applications from all backgrounds, abilities and communities. If you require any accommodations or adjustments to our interview process, please reach out to jobs@datatonic.com and we will do our best to assist you.

Title: (Senior) Product Owner/Manager - Information Retrieval Platform
Description:
Applications are considered on a rolling basis Gothenburg

We are looking for a passionate and seasoned Product Owner to join our Product Management organization and lead our information retrieval platform development.

At Meltwater, we are creating the next generation media intelligence solutions for a global client base. In support of this vision, the information retrieval team operates and evolves the most central part of Meltwater’s vast library of content, playing a key role in the storage and access of all of the company’s current editorial, social, and broadcast media assets by building a platform that provides petabyte-scale search and analytics capabilities.

This mission is central to Meltwater’s growth, highly visible to executives, and plays a strategic role in our Enterprise offerings. As Product Owner/Manager for this team, you will work directly with sales, customers, and other product owners to drive product delivery and inspire the team to build the best products possible. You will have a direct impact on product direction, positioning, and, ultimately our business strategy.

If you are intrigued by the opportunity of helping companies around the globe improve communication with their employees by extracting business-critical insights from millions of online conversations and engaging their employees in relevant news, you should continue reading.

What you'll do

Confidently articulate and evolve the vision for the information retrieval platform.

Work closely with stakeholders across the organization to ensure that you and the team provide for the company’s short- and long-term goals.

Helps the team realize the value of their work and appreciate how their deliverables impact the business.

Define, track, and interpret critical metrics to ensure your team is doing the right things while not spreading out too thin. A healthy balance of innovation, support, and maintenance is key for all successful teams at Meltwater.

Manage your own and the team’s availability - given stakeholders across the globe, we sometimes need to join/host meetings outside typical office hours.

Represent your product both internally and externally. Acting as a key evangelist and product expert.

The position is offered in our office in Gothenburg, Sweden. We are remote-friendly but expect you to come to the office from time to time to work with your colleagues in person.

SKILLS & REQUIREMENTS

Who you are

You have at least 3+ years of experience managing and developing software products as a PM/PO in an agile product development environment.

You have experience working in a B2B SaaS or platform business environment.

You are an interdisciplinary thinker, skilled at blending different perspectives in pursuing a mission.

You have a proven ability to understand complex business problems, apply strong analytical skills, and create an effective strategy.

You have a proven track record of delivering technical solutions for large-scale business problems.

You have excellent written and verbal communication skills; you can effectively communicate at varying levels of technical detail with all levels and types of internal stakeholders in one-on-one and group situations.

You have excellent leadership and relationship-building skills.

You are good at sorting out ambiguity.

You are fluent in English.

Bonus Skills

Scrum Product Owner certification (CSPO).

Experience with data mining, search engines, and big data analytics.

Experience defining products & solutions containing large data sets from multiple sources.

Background in Big Data, specifically around volume, velocity, and veracity.

Professional background includes software development.

GREAT PLACE TO WORK

Competitive Salary

Fresh fruits & free drinks

Internal hackathons

Personal Branding Support

Ergonomic desks and chairs

Great hardware

Opportunities to travel in Europe and the U.S.

Open Source Contributions

Conferences and Tech Talks

ABOUT THE COMPANY

Meltwater, a pioneer of media intelligence and now Outside Insight, gives businesses the information advantage they need to stay ahead. More than 30,000 companies have used Meltwater’s media intelligence to stay on top of billions of online conversations and extract relevant insights to strategically manage their brands. Meltwater is dedicated to personal, global service built on the local expertise of 55 offices across six continents. Meltwater is also committed to fostering the data science ecosystem through MEST, a pan-African entrepreneurial program and incubator, and Shack15, a global data science community. Learn more at meltwater.com.

All of our solutions are fully web-based, offered as a service, and based on a modern technology stack. This is your opportunity to be part of a small agile team within a big multinational organization!

We are more than 2000 people across the globe, so there is a lot going on. We believe in diversity and inclusion, and building teams with a wide variety of backgrounds and perspectives. This approach not only raises the quality of our products for our customers, but makes collaboration along the way much more fun.

Read our underthehood blog to see which problems our engineers are solving. Also have a look at what life is like at Meltwater and visit our company profiles on LinkedIn, Xing, Facebook, and Twitter.

Equal Opportunity

Meltwater is firmly committed to affording equal employment opportunities to all candidates and employees alike without regard to race, color, religion, age, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or gender expression, marital status disability, veteran status and we treat each individual with respect and dignity.

The “EEO is the Law” poster is available at: http://bit.ly/2KBm9Ei

And “EEO is the Law Supplement” poster is available at: http://bit.ly/2Kmxnxd

Title: Product Manager for Risk Intelligence – Securitas Digital
Description:
Securitas Group
Strongly united by the purpose “We help make your world a safer place”, Securitas successfully integrates technology, people and knowledge to offer protective services to clients all over the world. Securitas offers security services by combining expertise in on-site, mobile and remote guarding with electronic security and experience in fire and safety. The group has 345,000 employees in 47 markets worldwide.
Securitas Digital
Securitas vision is to become the Intelligent Protective Services Partner through being client centric, data driven, and people focused. Our protective services help make your world a safer place.
Securitas Digital is a global business unit that aims to position Securitas as the security industry’s technology & client experience leader. Based on an established innovation capability, we accelerate our digitalization and client experience journey by focusing on Securitas’ digital products and services.

Risk Intelligence
An area that is at the forefront of modern security and is powered by AI modelling. Risk Intelligence’s purpose is to ground our client’s intuition in real-time models to anticipate and respond to their site’s risk exposure, reported incidents, and external events.
In this team we work with data-driven products and capabilities that leverage the collective report data from Securitas’ officers and real-time data, providing valuable internal insights to our clients.
With cutting-edge machine learning capabilities, we are producing new insights to the security industry, and we are already live with products in two countries. As we are expanding our services and reach during 2023, the focus on identifying and providing end-user value remains essential to the goal.
We are now looking for an experienced product manager that can join the team and lead the current expansion and identify new value propositions in this exciting area.

What you will do:
Be responsible for the portfolio backlog and take active part in product priorities based on user needs and market fit
Be responsible for roadmap, vision and strategy for your product and for the capabilities under your responsibility
Formulate requirements for your products
Work in close collaboration with engineering, data science/engineering, UX, roll-out and commercialisation
You will be working structured with stakeholder management in the large and global company that Securitas is
You will be responsible for defining, identifying, collection and tracking of the right product metrics
Create business plans for your area and be responsible for the budget for your product


What we want you to bring:
More than 5 years of Software Product Management experience
Experience in taking a product from concept to launch, creating product roadmaps and product visions
Experience from working in a fast-paced agile environment
You should have experience from driving commercial digital products on a large international scale
Understand data and be able to do initial analyses and translate it to benefits for our clients
You should have an interest and an knowledge of AI and understand differences and the application of e.g. NLP and machine learning
You can engage with complex technical contexts to help your team make good decisions, understand trade-offs and represent your domain to a broad audience.
A bonus if you have experience from the security industry
Strong stakeholder management and leadership skills
Strong ability to work with virtual teams
Strong verbal and written communication
Multi culture awareness and understanding
Fluent in English
Experience from presenting to senior executive audiences
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related technical field, or equivalent practical experience

Who you are
These are the characteristics that we are looking for
Engaged
Pragmatic
Solution oriented
Delivery focused
Collaborative / Socially oriented
Communicative
Available (on site in Malmö and Stockholm to some extent will be required.)
Market aware
Solid understanding of applied risk management (vocabulary, terminology and usage in an organizational context).

What we offer
At Securitas we believe in doing the right thing and doing it well. For our customers and our employees. Our employees come from all walks of life and bring with them a multitude of talents and perspectives. We aim for diverse representation throughout the company, and we are committed to equal pay, safe working conditions, gender balance and an inclusive work environment with a wide range of skills and development opportunities.

If it all sounds good for you, don’t hesitate and apply!

Title: Ubuntu Quality Engineering Manager
Description:
We are looking for an engineering manager for our Ubuntu Quality Engineering team, with a mission to take Linux distro quality to a new level through automation and large-scale data analysis.
As the Ubuntu Quality Engineering Manager, you must be passionate about the future of Ubuntu, mindful of the dynamics of the open source ecosystem, and equally aware of mission critical requirements. You will work closely with the various teams involved in creating Ubuntu and influence their practices to improve quality in every step of Ubuntu engineering. Your goal is to rethink the way a Linux distro approaches quality - bringing together automation, third-party analysis tooling, feedback loops from the community and user base, and our own test capabilities. Your team will monitor, develop and improve the quality of the Ubuntu System, to drive quality excellence and best devops practices among Ubuntu Desktop, Server, Containers and VM at package, system and cluster levels.
As an engineering manager at Canonical your role is technical but your focus is your team. You are expected to help them grow as engineers, do important and satisfying work, and work well with colleagues and community. Technical leadership experience and a background in software engineering are necessary prerequisites for this role. You will be expected to lead, challenge, and develop strong engineers, positively influence the culture, facilitate technical delivery, and work with your team on strategy and execution.
What you'll do
Set and manage expectations with other engineering teams, management, and external stakeholders
Advocate and advance modern, agile software development practices
Develop and evangelize great engineering and organizational practices
Setup and maintain continuous integration for all supported deliverables
Define and monitor quality metrics
Develop a team with a culture of high quality and performance
Work from home with international travel twice per year for up to two weeks
Who you are
You have a strong software engineering, Linux, and open source background
Your technical knowledge includes C/C++, Python programming and Shell scripting
You have experience with data science to support data-driven quality strategies
You have experience with quality processes and continuous integration tools and principles
You have engineering management experience and enjoy growing people
Valued additional experience
A good understanding of Debian packaging and snaps will be valuable
Familiarity with an agile development environment
We are proud to foster a workplace free from discrimination. Diversity of experience, perspectives, and background create a better work environment and better products.Whatever your identity, we will give your application fair consideration.
#LI-Remote #stack

Title: Google Cloud Platform (GCP) Architect
Description:
As a GCP Data Architect you will join our team of Scandinavia's leading Data, Analytics & AI experts, which gives us the right competence to help our customers succeed on their journey towards a data-driven decision. We are all passionate about data!
What You'll Do
Insights & Data is a large team of specialists, and we offer different types of services - consulting, development of digital strategies and roadmaps, design and implementation of AI, IoT, Analytics and Data Management solutions. Of course, supported by cloud architecture and cyber security.
As a GCP Data Architect, you will guide our clients toward data-driven decisions-making, by implementing optimal technical solutions while focusing on Google Cloud Platform.
Your workday will consist of different tasks such as:
Guiding our clients in the decision making of which platform and architecture to use
Integration of different data sources, modeling and loading of data
Optimizing different solutions (data warehouse, data lakehouse, machine learning) depending on the purpose
Helping our clients with data-driven business development all the way from strategic decision making to implemented solutions
To be able to be successful in the role we believe that you have strong communication and interpersonal skills.
We actively work with competence sharing and development, and you’ll belong to one or several competence areas where we actively share learnings within different areas of expertise. We offer a great environment for you to develop the career that you want!
Archicture is highly valued at Capgemini, and therefore we’ve invested a lot in educational architecture programs and communities where architects can share and develop ideas. So, if you’re interested in becoming an either a solutition architect or entreprise architecture, we have learning communities for you.
Who We Are
Capgemini Insights & Data, is the Nordic leader in Data, Analytics and AI. We are more than 300 consultants, distributed across offices in Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Helsingborg. Our services include consultancy within Data Platforms, Visual analytics, Data Trust, Data Science & AI, Advisory Services and Solution Services. Many of the Nordic market’s leading experts belong in our organization, putting us in the best possible position to help our clients succeed in their journey towards a data-driven enterprise. We offer our clients everything from local deliveries to global transformation projects, where our considerable size in the Nordics gives us the competence and the capacity to truly make a difference.
What you bring
Knowledgeable in Architecting and designing solutions leveraging GCP components like BigQuery, Dataflow, PubSub, BigTable, Rest API frameworks and Kubernetes (GKE)
Knowledgeable from acting as GCP Architect in Architecting applications and SME in multiple projects
Designing secure and compliance architecture, ensuring operations reliability
Knowledgeable in GitHub, CI/CD (Cloud Build, Terraform)
What we see as qualifying:
Hands on experience from development of various services in either of languages preferably as Java, JavaScript/Node.js, Golang and/or Python
Collaborative software engineering practices (Agile, Scrum, DevOps)
Understanding of event-based and microservice Architecture
Knowledgeable in Infrastructure, Network and Security aspects

Title: Senior Consultant Retail - Business & Technology Solutions (BTS) - Stockholm, Helsingborg, Malmö
Description:

By joining BTS, you will have the opportunity to help shape the set-up, form the culture, and together decide on what is important to focus on initially and long term to create a dynamic, fun, and rewarding workplace.
As a Senior Consultant Retail in our CPRD (Consumer Products, Retail & Distribution) team, you work with some of the leading a most well-known brands within the Retail industry. You will play a leading role in complex client projects in the intersection of business and IT, advising and supporting our clients in their digital transformation journey.
The responsibilities will vary from project to project, you will for example:
Act as Subject Matter Expert within your area of expertise
Developing, implementing, and improving business processes
Design and implement technology solutions enabling business to take advantage of their current and emerging opportunities
You advise our customers in the areas of supply chain management, logistics, warehouse management, enterprise resource management, customer relationship management and Loyalty in multi-channel commerce (including eCommerce)
Support our sales organization in shaping and advising on new deals
With your individual strengths and your professional expertise, you will work on the further development of our service portfolio
What you'll bring:
Well-founded, industry-specific expertise from the Consumer Products & Retail industry, especially Consumer Products.
Knowledge of IT processes in retail (e.g. in the areas of SCM, Logistics, ERP, CRM, Loyalty, eCommerce)
You can contextualize and apply trends and technologies such as Cloud, Agile, AI, Machine Learning, Data Science, Warehouse Automation and Robotics.
Experience in Requirements elicitation and system design
Experience working as a consultant
Soft skills and Background:
You are characterized by your focus on results, your strategic thinking, your high level of self-motivation and customer orientation.
Good communicator with business and IT stakeholders
Comfortable working in a mixed client and Capgemini environment
Comfortable working in an agile environment
Bachelor or academic background preferred (or equivalent experience) - preferably in computer science.

Title: WE ARE RECRUITING A TECH LEAD TO MODELON, LUND!
Description:
Ready to make an impact with systems simulation? The future of modeling and simulation starts with you. Join our mission of revolutionizing simulation technology at an international, collaborative, and inclusive work environment!
Modelon is forming a new team in Lund for developing a new web app to intuitively set-up simulation and optimization experiments and visualize big data for decision making. Therefore, we need to recruit an experienced Tech Lead to set-up and lead this team.
Modelon has already developed a web app for building models and a backend for performing simulations on the cloud called Modelon Impact: This will be complemented by the experimentation web app that is targeted to a larger user category not involved in creating models but involved in using models to make model-based product design decisions.
The new web app will enable running thousands of simulations in order that our users can find the optimal selection of components and parametrization of their new product offers. Our users typically work with designing sustainable energy, automotive and aerospace solutions, i.e., wind power plants, solar power plants, carbon-capture technology, electric cars, and electric airplanes. They want to perform post processing of simulation results, Monte Carlo simulations, sensitivity analysis, optimizations, machine learning training, etc. The users need a convenient way to define workflows to simplify repetitive work. The vision includes being able to perform such tasks also from tablets and smart phones.
What will you do?
The work of the team involves defining the appropriate architecture and tool chain. Furthermore, feature design and UI design will be performed together with product management and with inputs from Modeldon's service and commercial departments and from customers. The work involves collaboration with modeling web app and backend teams to provide a coherent UX.
The work in the team will involve technologies such as ECMAScript, TypeScript, Python, PWA, RWA, React, data science, statistics, optimization, Plotly, 3D visualization, machine learning and Jenkins.
Ensure the delivery of our projects: It's a hands-on role so we expect you do development and code reviews. While full-time development is not part of the role, we encourage you to take part in the development activities of your choosing to keep your skills updated.
Collaborate closely with the Product Manager, Team Leads and Scrum Master, to make sure our projects are delivered efficiently and following our standards and best practices.
Nurture and assess developers assigned to you: Encourage curiosity and continuous learning in the area you are an expert in.
Provide insights to and collaborate closely with the CTO to improve the engineering skills of the team. Coordinate activities between all engineering areas.
Required skills and qualifications
5 years or more of professional development experience.
Experience in TypeScript, Python and React.
Prior experience as Team Lead/Tech Lead/Architect is a plus.
Enjoy working on challenging solutions and systems.
Believe that building great applications is not only about delivering code that "works", but involves thinking about reusability, maintainability, security, and performance.
Curious, structured, with a "Can do attitude" and a product mindset.
Enjoys collaboration within the team and with other departments.
Good at communicating in both Swedish and English.
Meritorious skills
Experience of Agile development and practices.
Jenkins, ECMAScript, PWA, RWA, data science, statistics, optimization, 3D Visualization and machine learning.
About Modelon
Modelon offers systems modeling and simulation software that accelerates product innovation, development, and operations in a range of industries. We believe that we can only achieve excellence when we work together. Our teams are closely aligned, and we encourage cross-team collaboration at every opportunity. Modelon is revolutionizing the engineering design industry by offering technologies and services that enable customers to leverage system simulation. Modelon's flagship product, Modelon Impact, is a cloud system simulation platform that helps engineers virtually design, analyze, and simulate physical systems. Our team brings deep industry expertise and is dedicated to guiding our customers in creating innovative technologies at their respective organizations. Headquartered in Lund, Sweden, Modelon is a global company with offices in Germany, India, Japan, Prague, and the United States. Read more about us here: https://modelon.com
Contact and Information
In this recruitment, Modelon collaborates with Experis IT, with extensive experience in recruiting specialists and managers within IT. For questions about the position, please contact recruitment consultant Jenny Flygare, jenny.flygare@se.experis.com, 070-2557143 or Luka Jovovic, luka.jovovic@se.experis.com 072-2058887. You apply for the position via the application link at www.experis.se.
Welcome with your application!
